INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('maximum', '[\'mæksɪməm]', 'n.最大量；最大限度；最高点 adj.最高的；最大极限的', '1. This hall holds a maximum of seventy people. 这厅最多容纳七十人。 2. The child turned the volume up to the maximum. 小孩把音量转到了最大。 3. It is the maximum the insurance company will pay. 这是保险公司所能付给的最大金额。 4. Our goal is to achieve the maximum of efficiency. 我们的目标是取得最高的效率。 5. The maximum price we can pay is 50 pence per yard. 我们所能出的最高价格是每码50便士。', '名词复数: maximums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brave', '[breɪv]', 'adj.勇敢的；英勇的 v.勇敢地面对', '1. I think you are very brave. 我认为你非常勇敢。 2. The soldier\'s brave deeds brought him honor and glory. 士兵的勇敢事迹为他带来了荣耀和赞美。 3. Let us remember the brave who died for the peace of the world. 让我们永远怀念为世界和平献身的勇士们。 4. They made a brave stand against the enemy. 他们对敌人进行了英勇的抵抗。', '副词: bravely 比较级: braver 最高级: bravest 名词: braveness 过去式: braved 过去分词: braved 现在分词: braving 第三人称单数: braves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('naval', '[\'neɪvl]', 'adj.海军的；军舰的', '1. It was unable to turn around at the West end of Chambers Field at the Norfolk Naval Station. 它是不能在诺福克海军的车站室领域的西繁华区回过头的。 2. Or you hear about a naval vessel that\'s up for auction or a vessel that\'s been confiscated by the Customs for smuggling. 或许你会听说有一条海军的船要拍卖，或是有一条让海关没收的走私船。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outline', '[\'aʊtlaɪn]', 'n.大纲；轮廓 vt.概述；画出轮廓', '1. He wrote down the outline of his lecture. 他写下演讲的提纲。 2. She drew the outline with a sure hand. 她笔力雄健地画出了轮廓。 3. He saw the outline of the house in the moonlight. 在月光下,他看到了那座屋子的轮廓。 4. At the interview, she outlined what i would be doing. 在谈话时,她概述了我将要干的工作。', '过去式: outlined 过去分词: outlined 现在分词: outlining 第三人称单数: outlines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poetry', '[\'poʊətri]', 'n.诗歌；诗意；诗集', '1. Poetry helps to interpret life. 诗有助于阐释人生的意义。 2. I spent all my spare time reading poetry. 我所有的业余时间都用在诗歌阅读上。 3. Professor Lee will give us a lecture on poetry. 李教授将就诗歌对我们作学术讲演。 4. In poetry the rose is often a metaphor for love. 玫瑰在诗中通常作为爱的象征。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('humble', '[\'hʌmbl]', 'adj.谦逊的；粗陋的；卑下的；微末的 vt.使 ... 卑下；贬低', '1. Knowledge makes humble, ignorance makes proud. 博学使人谦逊，无知使人骄傲。 2. The duke did well by people in humble stations. 那位公爵善待地位低下的人。 3. The family lived in a humble cottage. 这户人家住在一所简陋的农舍里。 4. You are welcome to my humble home. 非常欢迎您光临寒舍。 5. She\'ll humble you to the dust. 她一定要把你糟蹋得一文不值。', '副词: humbly 比较级: humbler 最高级: humblest 名词: humbleness 过去式: humbled 过去分词: humbled 现在分词: humbling 第三人称单数: humbles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('provoke', '[prə\'voʊk]', 'vt.激怒；惹起；驱使', '1. If you provoke the dog, he may bite you. 你如果激怒了这条狗，它可能会咬你。 2. Don\'t provoke the animals in the cage. 不要激怒笼中的动物。 3. His rudeness provoked me to strike him. 他的粗鲁惹得我揍了他。 4. Such a questionable assertion is sure to provoke criticism. 这种有问题的主张肯定会招致非议。', '副词: provokingly 过去式: provoked 过去分词: provoked 现在分词: provoking 第三人称单数: provokes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hardware', '[\'hɑːrdwer]', 'n.五金器具；[计] 硬件；武器装备', '1. They carried a vast inventory of hardware. 他们带着大量的五金器具存货。 2. My house stands cheek by jowl with a hardware shop. 我家紧靠一家五金商店。 3. I know nothing about computer hardware. 我对计算机硬件一窍不通。 4. We deal in hardware but not software. 我们只经营硬件而不经营软件。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sociable', '[\'soʊʃəbl]', 'adj.好交际的；社交的', '1. Roger is a very sociable person. 罗杰是个非常好交际的人。 2. But they were a sociable family and liked their neighbors, especially the O\'Hara girls. 不过塔尔顿家是个好交际的家庭，喜欢和邻居尤其是奥哈拉家的姑娘拉来往。 3. As a whole they are friendly and sociable people. 作为一个整体，他们是友善而好社交的人。 4. Sociable people, those who like to be with others, like red. 喜欢社交的人，喜欢和他人在于起的人都喜欢红色。', '副词: sociably 名词: sociableness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thoughtful', '[\'θɔːtfl]', 'adj.深思的；体贴的', '1. He had a thoughtful look on his face. 他脸上露出深思的表情。 2. The young girl in the picture has a thoughtful and solemn mien. 画中的年轻女孩带着一副沉思而又严肃的神态。 3. It\'s most thoughtful of you. 您想得真周到。 4. A thoughtful present is always appreciated. 一个体贴的礼物总会令人感激。', '副词: thoughtfully 名词: thoughtfulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('perceive', '[pər\'sːv]', 'v.注意到；觉察到；认为；理解', '1. I plainly perceive some objections remain. 我清楚地察觉到还有一些反对意见。 2. We can perceive his sorrow by the looks on his face. 我们从他的表情中觉察出悲伤。 3. Indeed, this problem is greater than one may perceive. 确实，这个问题远大于你所能感知到的。 4. They perceive television as entertainment. 他们将电视视为娱乐。', '形容词: perceivable 副词: perceivably 名词: perceiver 过去式: perceived 过去分词: perceived 现在分词: perceiving 第三人称单数: perceives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gaol', '[dʒeɪl]', 'n.监狱 v.(使)坐牢；监禁 =jail(美).', '1. Since he escaped from gaol, Tom has been living on a razor\'s edge, terrified of recapture. 汤姆越狱后,时时如惊弓之鸟,生怕再次被捕。 2. Strikes by prison officers underline the need for reform in our gaols. 监狱工作人员罢工一事，突出地表明我们的监狱制度需要改革。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fly', '[flaɪ]', 'v.飞；坐飞机；驾驶；逃跑；悬挂 n.苍蝇；飞行；两翼昆虫', '1. The aircraft was flying above thick fog. 飞机在浓雾上空飞行。 2. How time flies! 时间过得真快！ 3. She will drive to, but fly back from, London. 她将坐汽车去伦敦，坐飞机从伦敦回来。 4. Only experienced pilots fly large passenger aircraft. 只有有经验的飞行员才能驾驶大型客机。 5. Waiter, there\'s a fly in my soup! That\'s OK, Sir, there\'s no extra charge! 服务员,汤里有只苍蝇!我知道,先生,我们没有另收钱。', '形容词: flyable 名词复数: flies 过去式: flew 过去分词: flown 现在分词: flying 第三人称单数: flies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('waitress', '[\'weɪtrəs]', 'n.女侍者；女服务员', '1. The waitress received a handsome tip. 女侍者收到了数量可观的小费。 2. A waitress came in, carrying tea on a tray. 一名女侍者走进来，手端放着茶的托盘。 3. A waitress put a glass of water in front of him. 一名女服务员迎上来在他面前放了一杯水。 4. The waitress brought us two pats of butter. 女服务员给我们端来两小块黄油。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crucial', '[\'kruːʃl]', 'adj.决定性的；关键的', '1. Her work has been crucial to the project\'s success. 她的工作对项目的成功至关重要。 2. It is crucial that we get this right. 我们把这个问题弄明白是极其重要的。 3. Trust is crucial for successful friendship. 相互信任是维系友谊的关键。 4. The battle had reached a crucial stage. 战斗已到了关键阶段。', '副词: crucially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mass', '[mæs]', 'n.大量；块；众多 adj.大规模的；群众的 v.集中 Mass. n.弥撒曲；弥撒', '1. After harvest we will have a mass of rice. 秋收后，我们将获得大量稻谷。 2. There were masses of dark clouds in the sky. 天上有朵朵乌云。 3. Football stars seem larger-than-life to the mass of fans. 在众多的球迷看来,足球明星是十分杰出的。 4. Modern education is a mass enterprise. 现代教育是一项大规模的企业。 5. Crowds massed along the road where the king would pass. 群众聚集在国王要经过的街道旁。 6. The priest sings Mass. 牧师吟唱弥撒曲。', '过去式: massed 过去分词: massed 现在分词: massing 第三人称单数: masses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coincide', '[ˌkoʊɪn\'saɪd]', 'vi.一致；同时发生；符合', '1. They didn\'t coincide in opinion. 他们的意见不统一。 2. Our opinions did not coincide on this case. 在这个案例上,我们的意见不一致。 3. My religious beliefs don\'t coincide with yours. 我的宗教信仰跟你的不一样。 4. Their stories coincided. 他们的叙述一致.', '过去式: coincided 过去分词: coincided 现在分词: coinciding 第三人称单数: coincides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gracious', '[\'ɡreɪʃəs]', 'adj.亲切的；高尚的；仁慈的；和蔼的；优雅的', '1. The Queen greeted the crowed with a gracious smile. 女王带着亲切的微笑向人群致意。 2. I received a gracious letter of acknowledgement. 我收到一封有礼貌的感谢信。 3. I\'ll be greatly honoured by your gracious presence. 如蒙光临，不胜荣幸。 4. Insist the gracious living style to experience the essential life spirit. 坚持以高尚的生活方式，体验生活本质的精神态度。', '副词: graciously 名词: graciousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('milk', '[mɪlk]', 'n.奶；牛奶；乳汁 v.挤乳；产乳；榨取', '1. A baby vomits milk from repletion. 婴儿吃饱会吐奶。 2. She dribbled some milk onto the cereal. 她把一些奶滴在燕麦片上。 3. The cat lapped up the milk. 猫舔食牛奶。 4. I am boiling the milk. 我正在煮牛奶。 5. The farmer whistled as he milked. 农夫一边挤奶一边吹口哨。', '名词: milker 过去式: milked 过去分词: milked 现在分词: milking 第三人称单数: milks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('employer', '[ɪm\'plɔɪər]', 'n.雇主', '1. He sued his employer for wrongful dismissal. 他控告雇主非法解雇他。 2. The university is a major employer in the area. 该大学是这一地区的大雇主。 3. He was in his employer\'s good graces. 他深得雇主的赏识。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('limited', '[\'lɪmɪtɪd]', 'adj.有限的；被限制的 动词limit的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. We had only limited communion with the natives. 我们与本地人的交往有限。 2. We have limited funds and several competing claims. 我们的基金有限而争相申请的却有几处。 3. His intelligence is rather limited. 他的智力相当有限。 4. A limited number of cars is available. 汽车使用数目有限制。', '副词: limitedly 名词: limitedness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('raw', '[rɔː]', 'adj.未加工的；生的；原始的；湿冷的 n.触到某人的痛处', '1. We imported raw rubber from Malaysia. 我们从马来西亚进口生胶。 2. Do you want your vegetables cooked or raw? 你要把蔬菜煮熟还是生吃？ 3. The factory is in frequent scarcity of raw materials. 这个工厂经常原料不足。 4. She makes use of people she meets as raw material for her fiction. 她把她所遇见的人们作为她创作小说的素材。 5. She was always ready to catch people on the raw and hold them up to ridicule. 她专爱揭短处, 挑人长相。', '副词: rawly 比较级: rawer 最高级: rawest 名词: rawness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('region', '[\'riːdʒən]', 'n.地区；范围；领域；地带；地域', '1. Most of the countries in the region have unstable economies. 这个地区大多数国家的经济都不稳定。 2. I guess there are much less people in the Arctic regions than here. 我想北极地区的人要比这里的少得多。 3. The region near the erupting volcano was evacuated rapidly. 火山爆发处附近已迅速撤空。 4. These small spiced cakes are a peculiarity of the region. 这些别有风味的小蛋糕是该地的特产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('northeast', '[\'nɔːθ\'iːst]', 'n.东北 adj.东北的；向东北的；来自东北的 adv.向东北；来自东北', '1. At this point the road turns northeast. 路在这里转向东北。 2. The Northeast is the granary of the country. 东北是祖国的粮仓。 3. It is a strategic pass to the northeast. 这里是通往东北的要隘。 4. Hereby he is presenting the fellows in Northeast China. 在这里他向我们呈现的是东北的父老乡亲。 5. They voyaged northeast for several days. 他们向东北航行了几天。', '形容词: northeastern');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('season', '[\'siːzn]', 'n.季节；赛季；旺季；时期 v.给 ... 调味；适应；风干', '1. Winter is the coldest season in a year. 冬季是一年中最冷的季节。 2. He will captain the basketball team next season. 他将在下个赛季担任该篮球队的队长。 3. Holiday prices are lower out of season. 在度假淡季，度假费用较低。 4. The last three years have been a good season for the company. 过去三年一直是公司的兴旺时期。 5. You can season the soup with salt and pepper. 你可以用盐和胡椒来调汤的味道。', '过去式: seasoned 过去分词: seasoned 现在分词: seasoning 第三人称单数: seasons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('security', '[sə\'kjʊrəti]', 'n.安全；保证；证券；债券；抵押；防护措施', '1. I\'ll undertake for your security. 我将保证你的安全。 2. The visitors were secarched for security reasons. 为了安全起见,来宾受到了检查。 3. Our own actions are our security. 我们的行为是自己的保证。 4. He traded in securities and became rich. 他做证券交易发了财。', '名词复数: securities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invent', '[ɪn\'vent]', 'vt.发明；捏造', '1. Can you tell me who invented the telephone? 你能告诉我是谁发明了电话？ 2. He always strives to invent something new. 他一直努力要发明新东西。 3. The fact was that China was the first country to invent paper. 事实是中国是发明纸的第一个国家。 4. We must invent an excuse for our absence. 我们必须为缺席编造一个藉口。', '形容词: inventible 名词: inventor 过去式: invented 过去分词: invented 现在分词: inventing 第三人称单数: invents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dismay', '[dɪs\'meɪ]', 'n.沮丧；绝望 vt.使 ... 沮丧；使 ... 惊愕', '1. The enemy retreated in perfect dismay. 敌人沮丧地退去。 2. To my dismay, he made the same mistakes. 让我感到沮丧的是，他又犯了同样的错误。 3. He watched the burning bouse with dismay. 他绝望地看着着火的房子。 4. The teacher was dismayed at the students\' lack of response. 老师对学生的毫无反应感到沮丧。', '副词: dismayingly 过去式: dismayed 过去分词: dismayed 现在分词: dismaying 第三人称单数: dismays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('equality', '[i\'kwɑːləti]', 'n.同等；平等；[数]等式', '1. In some countries black people do not have equality with white people. 在某些国家黑人没有和白人同等的权利。 2. Genuine racial equality still seems light-years away. 真正的种族平等似乎仍遥遥无期。 3. The country\'s constitution embodies the ideals of freedom and equality. 这个国家的宪法体现了自由和平等的理想。 4. Martin Luther King made many adversaries in his nonviolent quest for equality. 马丁·路德·金在以非暴力手段寻求平等的过程中树立了许多敌人。', '名词复数: equalities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('depend', '[dɪ\'pend]', 'vi.依赖；依靠；取决于', '1. Children depend on their parents for food and clothing. 小孩依赖他们的父母供给衣食。 2. He is a man whom you can depend on. 他是个你可以信赖的人。 3. The country depends heavily on its tourist trade. 这个国家的经济在很大程度上依靠其旅游业。 4. I have no one but you to depend on. 除了你，我没有可依靠的人。', '过去式: depended 过去分词: depended 现在分词: depending 第三人称单数: depends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('maybe', '[\'meɪbi]', 'adv.或许；也许；可能', '1. Maybe these nutrients are helpful to your health. 或许这些营养品对你的健康有帮助。 2. Maybe it will work. 也许这个办法会有效。 3. Maybe some other time. 也许下一次吧。 4. Maybe that\'s what I\'ll do. 这大概正是我要做的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slam', '[slæm]', 'v.砰地关上；猛放；猛烈攻击 n.砰然声；猛烈抨击 n.满贯', '1. He closed the door with a slam. 他砰的一声关上门。 2. He slammed the papers down on my desk and angrily walked out. 他把文件使劲扔在我的桌子上便怒气冲冲地走了出去。 3. Lincoln tried to lift his opponent off the ground and slam him hard on his back. 林肯试着把他的对手从地上提起，然后给其后背猛烈一击。 4. He threw his books down with a slam. 他砰然一声将书摔在桌上。 5. I still have two finesses to make a grand slam. 我还有两张飞牌来完成大满贯。', '过去式: slammed 过去分词: slammed 现在分词: slamming 第三人称单数: slams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('favorable', '[\'feɪvərəbəl]', 'adj.有利的；顺利的；良好的；赞同的', '1. The conditions are favorable for opening a new business. 各种条件有利于开办新企业。 2. He made several favorable comments about their candidate. 他对他们的候选人发表了一些有利的评论。 3. \"Our expedition made a favorable beginning. 我们远航开始的时候很顺利。 4. The book met with a favorable reception. 此书受到好评。', '副词: favorably 名词: favorableness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dawn', '[dɔːn]', 'n.黎明；曙光；开端；破晓 vi.开始出现；破晓；逐渐明白', '1. We set sail at dawn and headed for New York. 我们在黎明起程，直驶纽约。 2. Diana aroused them just before dawn. 戴安娜在黎明前唤醒了他们。 3. I can see the dawn of the better day for humanity. 我已经看到了人类美好日子的曙光。 4. The sky was pink with the first glimmer of the dawn. 天空因第一丝曙光而呈淡红色。 5. A new era is dawning. 一个新的时代开始出现了。', '过去式: dawned 过去分词: dawned 现在分词: dawning 第三人称单数: dawns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prosecute', '[\'prɑːsɪkjuːt]', 'vt.起诉；告发；从事；彻底进行 vi.起诉；担任检察官', '1. Trespassers will be prosecuted. 闲人免进，违者必究。 2. He was prosecuted for exceeding the speed limit. 他被告发超速行驶。 3. He vowed that he would prosecute them for fraud. 他郑重宣布将起诉他们犯有欺诈罪。 4. We should never prosecute the innocent. 我们决不应控告无辜的人。 5. The police decided not to prosecute. 警方决定不予起诉。', '形容词: prosecutable 过去式: prosecuted 过去分词: prosecuted 现在分词: prosecuting 第三人称单数: prosecutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overwhelm', '[ˌoʊvər\'welm]', 'vt.打击；压倒；使感动；淹没；打败', '1. No difficulty can overwhelm us. 困难压不倒我们。 2. If I cannot overwhelm with my quality, I will overwhelm with my quantity. 如果我不能以质量压倒，我就一定要以数量压倒。 3. Your kindness quite overwhelmed me. 你的好意使我感激难言。 4. The village was overwhelmed when the floods came. 这个村庄在洪水泛滥时被淹没了。', '过去式: overwhelmed 过去分词: overwhelmed 现在分词: overwhelming 第三人称单数: overwhelms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('confer', '[kən\'fɜːr]', 'v.商讨；授予，赐予', '1. I must confer with my lawyer before I decide. 我必须先同我的律师商量一下才能做出决定。 2. I will confer with him on the subject. 我将和他商议这件事。 3. The Queen conferred knighthood on several distinguished men. 女王将爵士头衔授予几位杰出人士。 4. The university confers master degree on her. 学校授予她硕士学位。', '形容词: conferrable 名词: conferment 过去式: conferred 过去分词: conferred 现在分词: conferring 第三人称单数: confers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ample', '[\'æmpl]', 'adj.丰富的；宽敞的；充足的', '1. He has got ample stage experience, and won\'t get stage fright. 他有丰富的舞台经验，不会怵场的。 2. The region developed by leaps and bounds because of its ample mineral resources. 这个地区由于有丰富的矿藏,所以发展得很快。 3. The house has an ample parlor. 这座房子有宽敞的客厅。 4. Our sitting room is ample and bright. 我们的居室宽敞明亮。', '副词: amply 比较级: ampler 最高级: amplest 名词: ampleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('launch', '[lɔːntʃ]', 'v.发起；推出（新产品）；发射；使(船)下水 n.发射；产品推介', '1. We were going to launch a counterattack. 我们准备发起反攻。 2. The company researched the market demand and decided to launch their new product. 这家公司调查了市场需求，决定推出新产品。 3. The people all over the country exulted in the success in launching a new satellite. 全国人民为成功地发射了一颗新的人造卫星而欢欣鼓舞。 4. The oil tanker was launched last year. 那艘油轮去年下水了。 5. The launch was delayed by a technical hitch . 由于技术上出现临时故障而发射延期.', '过去式: launched 过去分词: launched 现在分词: launching 第三人称单数: launches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tuck', '[tʌk]', 'v.打摺；卷起；收拢；藏起；<俚>大吃 n.缝摺；船底后端；<俚>食品', '1. The baby\'s dress was beautifully tucked with tiny stitches. 婴儿衫的褶裥打得针脚细密，很漂亮。 2. Please help me tuck up my sleeves. 请帮我卷起袖子。 3. He was asleep before I tucked him in. 我还没来得及给他盖好被子，他就睡着了。 4. The hen tucked her head under her wing. 那母鸡把头缩在翅膀下。 5. The dress was too big, so Mother put a tuck in it. 衣服太大，所以妈妈在里面打了裥。', '过去式: tucked 过去分词: tucked 现在分词: tucking 第三人称单数: tucks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tremendous', '[trə\'mendəs]', 'adj.巨大的；惊人的', '1. He has a tremendous hold over his younger brother. 他对他弟弟很有影响。 2. She does her work with tremendous vigour. 她工作起来干劲十足。 3. The discovery caused a tremendous commotion in the scientific world. 那项发现在科学界引起极大的震动。 4. We got a tremendous surprise when she arrived. 她的到来使我们大吃一惊。', '副词: tremendously 名词: tremendousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lay', '[leɪ]', 'lie的过去式. v.放置；躺下；打赌；设计；击倒；产卵；使平静；压平 n.地形；位置；叙事短诗；交媾 adj.外行的；世俗的', '1. You may lay it on the table. 你可以把它放在桌子上。 2. I lay down not so much to sleep as to think. 我躺下来与其说是要睡觉，倒不如说是要思考。 3. I\'ll lay odds of three to one that he gets the job. 我以三比一的赔率打赌，他能得到那份工作。 4. He showed us how to lay out a printed page. 他告诉我们怎样设计版面。 5. He knows the lay of the land here. 他了解这里的地形。 6. A lay opinion as to the seriousness of the disease. 关于这种疾病的非专业的意见', '过去式: laid 过去分词: laid 现在分词: laying 第三人称单数: lays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('energy', '[\'enərdʒi]', 'n.精力；活力；能源', '1. Young people usually have more energy than the old. 青年人通常比老年人精力充沛。 2. Don\'t waste your time and energy on trifles. 别把你的时间和精力浪费在琐事上。 3. Auckland is a city full of energy. 奥克兰是个充满活力的城市。 4. The industry felt the effects of the energy crisis. 该工业受到能源危机的影响。', '名词复数: energies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feeble', '[\'fiːbl]', 'adj.虚弱的；无力的', '1. The bishop said it with a feeble voice as he woke. 主教醒过来，用虚弱的声音说出。 2. Feeble and uncertain securities were thrown upon the market. 虚弱的或者没有把握的证券都向市场抛售了。 3. Tighter credit conditions are sapping already feeble demand. 紧缩的信贷让本就无力的需求更加乏力。 4. He bleated out a feeble excuse. 他以微弱的声音作无力的辩解。', '副词: feebly 比较级: feebler 最高级: feeblest 名词: feebleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hover', '[\'hʌvər]', 'v.盘旋；徘徊；靠近（某事物），维持在某种不确定的状态 n.盘旋', '1. The hawk is hovering overhead. 鹰在头顶上盘旋。 2. After the alien spacecraft had hovered over the park for a short time, it vanished. 那只外星来的宇宙飞船在公园上空盘旋了一会儿之后就不见了。 3. He hovered nervously in the doorway. 他在门口紧张地来回踱步。 4. The mercury hovered around 35 Celsius degree. 水银温度计停留在摄氏35度左右。 5. He felt creeping of fate, the circling of wolves, the hover of vultures. 他感到厄运已经来到，豺狼正在包围，秃鹰也在盘旋。', '副词: hoveringly 名词: hoverer 过去式: hovered 过去分词: hovered 现在分词: hovering 第三人称单数: hovers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('collar', '[\'kɑːlər]', 'n.衣领；项圈；[机]轴环 vt.抓住；为 ... 戴上项圈；为 ... 上领子', '1. He grabbed my collar and pulled me towards him. 他抓住我的领子把我拉倒他面前。 2. He turned up his coat collar against the chill wind. 他竖起大衣领抵御寒风。 3. Where are the dog\'s collar and lead? 狗的颈圈和皮带哪去了？ 4. He seized the pickpocket by the collar. 他抓住那个扒手的衣领。', '形容词: collared 过去式: collared 过去分词: collared 现在分词: collaring 第三人称单数: collars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('finite', '[\'faɪnaɪt]', 'adj.有限的', '1. The world\'s resources are finite. 世界的资源是有限的。 2. Fortunately, the casualties were finite. 幸运的是，人员伤亡有限。 3. It is quite possible that space and time are finite. 很有可能空间和时间是有限的。 4. Any battery has a finite life span no matter what device it powers. 任何电池都具有有限的寿命，无论它具有多大的能量。', '副词: finitely 名词: finiteness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('light', '[laɪt]', 'n.光；光线；灯；打火机；领悟；浅色；天窗 adj.轻的；浅色的；明亮的；轻松的；容易的；清淡的 v.点燃；变亮；照亮 adv.清楚地；轻便地', '1. I try to see but I\'m blinded by the white light. 我试着去看，但是有道白光让我什么都看不到。 2. I can\'t read while you are standing in my light. 你挡住了我的光线，我没法看书。 3. He turned off the light before going out. 他出门前把灯关掉。 4. It was getting dark, so we switched on the light. 天色暗了,于是我们打开了灯。 5. This is a heavy box, and that is a light one. 这是一个重箱子,那是一个轻箱子。 6. I saw him enter the room, sit down and light a cigarette. 我看见他走进房间,坐了下来,点燃了一根香烟。', '比较级: lighter 最高级: lightest 过去式: lighted/lit 过去分词: lighted/lit 现在分词: lighting 第三人称单数: lights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dial', '[\'daɪəl]', 'n.拨号盘；刻度盘；日晷；钟面 v.拨号；打电话', '1. The phone number is on the dial. 号码就在拨号盘上。 2. Please clean the telephone set including the dial. 请将电话机清理一下,包括拨号盘。 3. The dial records very slight variations in pressure. 刻度盘显示出压力有微小变化。 4. Can you read the number on the dial? 你能读出刻度盘上的读数吗？ 5. Put in the money before dialing. 拨电话前先把钱放进去。', '名词: dialer 过去式: dialed/dialled 过去分词: dialed/dialled 现在分词: dialing/dialling 第三人称单数: dials/dials');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wash', '[wɑːʃ]', 'n.洗；洗涤 v.洗；洗涤；洗清', '1. This dress material shrinks in the wash. 这种衣料一洗要缩水。 2. We\'ll toss a coin to see who does the wash. 我们将掷币决定谁来洗衣服。 3. She has a large wash this week. 这星期她有大量衣服要洗。 4. Silk clothing should not use washing machines wash. 丝绸衣物不宜用洗衣机洗涤。 5. I must wash my hands before dinner. 吃饭前，我必须洗手。', '过去式: washed 过去分词: washed 现在分词: washing 第三人称单数: washes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('work', '[wɜːrk]', 'n.工作；职业；工作内容；职责；活计；工作所需的材料；工作地点；努力；工作成果；行为结果；作品 v.工作；做事；使工作；争取；管理；运行；操作；奏效；产生…影响；造成；抽搐；逐渐移动 [复]works：工厂；修建；机器部件；全套物品', '1. She had been out of work for a year. 她已失业一年了。 2. It\'s difficult to find work in present economic climate. 在目前这种经济气候下很难找到工作。 3. My line of work pays pretty well. 我的职业报酬颇丰厚。 4. Tell me something about your daily work. 告诉我你每天的工作内容。 5. She works for an engineering company. 她在一家工程技术公司工作', '过去式: worked/wrought 过去分词: worked/wrought 现在分词: working 第三人称单数: works');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('summon', '[\'sʌmən]', 'vt.召唤；召集；振奋', '1. I\'ve heard the residents of the Infernos will summon a Diety of Fire to honor any hero who brings them the Grail. 我听说地狱的居民会召唤烈火守护神来纪念为他们带来圣杯的英雄。 2. \"A man brags that he can summon the dead. 一个人炫耀说可以召唤死者灵魂。 3. The shareholders were summoned to a general meeting. 那些股东被召集去叁加股东大会。 4. They had to summon a second conference and change the previous decision. 他们不得不召集第二次会议，改变以前的决定。', '名词: summoner 过去式: summoned 过去分词: summoned 现在分词: summoning 第三人称单数: summons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thesis', '[\'θiːsɪs]', 'n.毕业论文；论文；论题；论点；命题', '1. Charles is writing his graduation thesis now. 查尔斯正在写毕业论文。 2. He has already started his thesis. 他已经开始写毕业论文了。 3. He wrote his doctoral thesis on electromagnetism. 他写有关电磁的博士论文。 4. He\'s been pegging away at his thesis for months. 他写论文已经忙了几个月了。', '名词复数: theses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accessory', '[ək\'sesəri]', 'n.附件；配件；同谋 adj.辅助的；附属的；同谋的', '1. He asked me to buy him some accessories for a car. 他让我给他买些汽车附件。 2. Every item shall include a standard complement of accessories and special tools to ensure the normal operation. 为保证设备的正常运转，每个品目都应包括一套标准定额的附件和专用工具。 3. This silk scarf is the perfect accessory for stylish summer evenings. 这条丝绸围巾对于这个时髦的夏日夜晚,是再合适不过的配件了。 4. He is Tom\'s accessory. 他是汤姆的帮凶。 5. He was using his accessory muscles of respiration. 他在用呼吸辅助肌进行呼吸。', '形容词: accessorial 副词: accessorily 名词: accessoriness 名词复数: accessories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chemical', '[\'kemɪkl]', 'adj.化学的 n.药品；化学物', '1. The government has banned the use of chemical weapons. 政府已经禁止使用化学武器。 2. A reactor is a container for chemical reaction. 反应器是进行化学反应的容器。 3. We are doing a chemical experiment. 我们正在做化学实验。 4. The industry produces agricultural chemicals. 这个工厂生产农药。', '副词: chemically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('throat', '[θroʊt]', 'n.嗓子；喉咙；颈部；嗓音 vt.低语；压着嗓子说(唱)', '1. I have a sore throat today. 我今天嗓子疼。 2. I have to clear my throat before I begin my speech. 在开始演讲之前,我得先清清嗓子。 3. I\'ve got a fish bone stuck in my throat. 有根鱼骨头卡在我的喉咙里。 4. He grabbed his enemy by the throat. 他掐住敌人的颈部。', '过去式: throated 过去分词: throated 现在分词: throating 第三人称单数: throats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thereafter', '[ˌðer\'æftər]', 'adv.其后；从那时以后', '1. Thereafter his idea of attending school gradually strengthened. 其后他求学的信念逐渐增强。 2. In the months thereafter he sank almost completely from view. 其后几个月他差不多完全消失了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('illuminate', '[ɪ\'luːmɪneɪt]', 'vt.照明；阐释；说明', '1. plastic food 2. A sudden smile illuminated her face. 突然的微笑使她容光焕发。 3. Footnotes illuminate the difficult passage of the book. 脚注中解释了书中许多难懂的道理。 4. Our interesting teacher could illuminate almost any subject we studied. 我们这位有趣的老师几乎能解释清楚我们所学的所有科目。', '副词: illuminatingly 过去式: illuminated 过去分词: illuminated 现在分词: illuminating 第三人称单数: illuminates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('string', '[strɪŋ]', 'n.线；弦；一串；字串 vt.串起；收紧；悬挂；系；扎；抽去筋；使紧张；使兴奋 vi.连成一串', '1. Puppets are worked by strings. 木偶是用线来操纵的。 2. The E string of the violin needs screwing up. 这只小提琴的E弦需要调紧些。 3. We have had a string of complaints about the program. 我们已经收到了对该节目的一连串投诉。 4. If the logon fails, an empty string is returned. 如果登录失败,则返回空字符串。 5. She strung the beads with a fine nylon. 她用细尼龙线把珠子串了起来。', '过去式: strung 过去分词: strung 现在分词: stringing 第三人称单数: strings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('furniture', '[\'fɜːrnɪtʃər]', 'n.家具；设备，装置；床罩；必要的附属品；【会计】家俬', '1. We will buy some furniture for our new house. 我们得给我们的新房子买些家具。 2. This old table is a valuable piece of furniture. 这张旧桌子是一件很珍贵的家具。 3. The antique furniture was made in 1700. 这件古老的家具是1700年制造的。 4. Children\'s furniture must withstand kicks and blows. 孩子用的家具必须经得起拳打脚踢。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sulfur', '[\'sʌlfə]', 'n.【U】硫(磺) v.用硫磺处理', '1. Sulfur can be used to make gunpowder. 硫磺可以用来制造火药。 2. A sulfide compound contains at least two sulfur atoms per molecule. 多硫化物每个分子中至少含有两个硫原子的一种硫化物 3. Because the removal of phosphorus and sulfur require special condition that can be met only by the basic process. 因为除去钢中的磷和硫需要一些特殊的条件，这些条件只有碱性法才能满足。', '过去式: sulfured/sulphured 过去分词: sulfured/sulphured 现在分词: sulfuring/sulphuring 第三人称单数: sulfurs/sulphurs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('photo', '[\'foʊtoʊ]', 'n.照片 v.拍照', '1. The photo has faded beyond recognition. 相片已经模糊，不能辨认。 2. The woman on the photo is my paternal grandmother. 照片上的这个妇人是我祖母。 3. When I waited for the No.13 line, I photoed them. 当我挺无聊地等待13号线时,我给他们拍了照。', '名词复数: photos 过去式: photoed 过去分词: photoed 现在分词: photoing 第三人称单数: photos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bitter', '[\'bɪtər]', 'adj.苦的；痛苦的；辛酸的；激烈的 adv.激烈地；极其 vt.使变苦 n.苦涩；苦酒；苦的东西', '1. The medicine has a bitter taste. 这药有苦味。 2. The defeat was a bitter pill to swallow. 那次失败是一次难以吞咽的苦果。 3. She wept bitter tears over the loss of her lover. 她为失去了她的情人而流下痛苦的眼泪。 4. Her voice took on a sudden bitter note. 她的声音带着一股出意料的辛酸语气。 5. He is bitter in his condemnation of terrorism. 他言辞激烈地谴责恐怖主义。 6. Green tea, unlike black tea, has not been oxidized and can easily turn bitter if not made properly. 绿茶与红茶不同，没有经过发酵氧化，如果处理不当很容易发涩变苦。 7. He has tasted the sweets and bitters of life. 他已尝遍了人生的甜酸苦辣。', '副词: bitterly 比较级: bitterer 最高级: bitterest 名词: bitterness 过去式: bittered 过去分词: bittered 现在分词: bittering 第三人称单数: bitters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('planet', '[\'plænɪt]', 'n.行星', '1. The Earth is a planet. 地球是一颗行星。 2. Mars is the fourth planet in order from the sun. 火星是太阳系的第四颗行星。 3. They claimed to have discovered a new planet. 他们宣称发现了一颗新的行星。 4. It is the only planet that we know harbors life. 它是我们所知唯一适合生物生存的行星。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fold', '[foʊld]', 'vt.包；折叠；交叉；拥抱 vi.翻倍；屈服；倒闭 n.折层；折痕', '1. Dark clouds folded the hills. 乌云笼罩着群山。 2. I folded the handkerchief and put it in my pocket. 我折好手绢，放进口袋里。 3. The paper should be folded in half. 这张纸应该对折。 4. The border guard folded his arms across his chest and glared the front. 边防战士双手交叉于胸前紧紧瞪着前方。 5. if a business folds, it closes because it is not able to make enough money. 如果有公司倒闭关门,那是因为它没办法赚取足够的钱。', '形容词: foldable 过去式: folded 过去分词: folded 现在分词: folding 第三人称单数: folds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hot', '[hɑːt]', 'adj.热的；辣的；强烈的 adv.激动地；趁热地 v.（使）变热', '1. A bowl of hot chicken soup is good for you. 喝一碗热鸡汤对你有好处。 2. The hot weather has soured the milk. 炎热的天气使牛奶变酸了。 3. This dish is a bit hot. 这道菜有些辣。 4. I could not bear with his hot temper. 我忍受不了他那急躁的脾气。 5. This food is best while eaten hot. 这道菜趁热吃最好。 6. I am going to hot up some food for you. 我去给你热点饭。', '比较级: hotter 最高级: hottest 名词: hotness 过去式: hotted 过去分词: hotted 现在分词: hotting 第三人称单数: hots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prior', '[\'praɪər]', 'adj.优先的；在前的；更重要的 adv.居先；在前', '1. He feels a prior obligation to his job as a journalist. 他觉得要优先为他的新闻记者的工作尽职。 2. Generally speaking, individuals who first appropriate part of a water supply have prior claim over those whose appropriation is later in time. 一般来说，先使用水资源的人比后使用者拥有更优先的权利。 3. The offer is subject to prior sale. 该报盘以未售出前为准。 4. His answer was tinted by his prior knowledge. 他的回答说明他先前就有所了解。 5. The golden octave holds within it all of the prior eight vibrations or planes within its field. 金色音阶内掌握着所有在前的八度音阶或它场内所有的层面。', '副词: priorly 名词: priority');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yearly', '[\'jɪrli]', 'adj.每年的 adv.每年地；一年一次地', '1. The yearly conference will be held next month. 年会下个月举行。 2. Many Greek cities had to send yearly tribute to Athens. 许多希腊城市不得不每年向雅典进贡。 3. Property values appreciated yearly. 财产价值每年都在增大。 4. The meeting is held yearly. 会议每年举行一次。', '名词复数: yearlies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('essence', '[\'esns]', 'n.精髓；本质；要素；香精', '1. Flavor of life is always sweet, because they always taste the essence of life. 生活的味道总是甜蜜的,因为他们总是品尝到生活的精髓。 2. Simplicity is the essence of good taste. 纯朴是情趣高尚的主要因素。 3. Caution is the essence of that man\'s character. 谨慎是那人性格的本质。 4. The two things are the same in outward form but different in essence. 那两样东西在外表上相同，但在本质上不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('message', '[\'mesɪdʒ]', 'n.消息；信息；要点；寓意 v.传递信息；通讯', '1. There is an important message for you from your brother. 你哥哥有个重要的消息要告诉你。 2. The message in the newspaper is unabridged. 报纸上的那则消息是没有经过删节的。 3. Did you deliver my message to my father? 你把我的信息传给我父亲了吗? 4. Christ\'s message was that God loved the world. 耶稣基督的启示就是神爱世人。 5. Please message the instruction by cable. 请用电报传送使用须知。', '过去式: messaged 过去分词: messaged 现在分词: messaging 第三人称单数: messages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disposal', '[dɪ\'spoʊzl]', 'n.处理；处置；布置', '1. We placed everything at his disposal. 我们把一切事情都交给他处理。 2. The disposal of rubbish is always a problem. 垃圾的处理总是个难题。 3. The safe disposal of nuclear waste is a major problem. 安全处置核废料是个大问题。 4. The money is at our own disposal. 这钱由我们自由支配使用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('property', '[\'prɑːpərti]', 'n.财产；所有物；地产，房地产；性质；道具', '1. The property was returned to the original owner. 财产已归还原主。 2. But you do not have the right to initiate force against the life, liberty and property of others. 但是,你没有发起强占其他人生命,自由和所有物的权利。 3. He has a large property in the county. 他在这个县有一大片地产。 4. Cheerfulness is a property of her personality. 开朗乐观是她的性格特征。', '形容词: propertyless 名词复数: properties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('living-room', '[\'lɪvɪŋ\'ruːm]', 'n.起居室', '1. The dining room is off the living room. 餐室通向起居室。 2. She sailed into my sitting room. 她步态优雅地走进我的起居室。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('donkey', '[\'dɔːŋki]', 'n.驴；愚蠢的人', '1. The bray of the donkey absorbed us. 驴叫声吸引了我们。 2. Our neighbour\'s female donkey is carrying a foal. 邻居的母驴怀上小驴驹了。', '名词复数: donkeys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reinforce', '[ˌriːɪn\'fɔːrs]', 'vt.加固；加强；增强；使更具说服力 vi.得到加强', '1. We will use metal strap to reinforce the outside. 我们会在纸箱外用金属带加固。 2. Any good speaker should be able to reinforce his argument with facts. 一个好的演讲者会用事实来加强他论点。 3. Public reaction will reinforce it. 社会反响会进一步增强它的作用。 4. This evidence reinforces my view that he is a spy. 这个证据证实了我认为他是间谍的这一看法。', '形容词: reinforceable');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('affect', '[ə\'fekt]', 'vt.影响；感动；作用', '1. How does interest rate affect the price of bonds? 利率如何影响债券的价格? 2. She was deeply affected by the sad story. 她深深被那个悲伤的故事感动了。 3. His charm doesn\'t affect or impress me. 他的魅力对我不起作用.', '名词: affecter 过去式: affected 过去分词: affected 现在分词: affecting 第三人称单数: affects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clap', '[klæp]', 'v.拍手；轻拍；鼓掌；啪地关上 n.霹雳声；轻拍；拍手声', '1. She clapped her hands in delight. 她高兴地拍手。 2. If you\'re happy, clap your hands. 如果感到幸福，你就拍拍手。 3. The gray-beard swept out an arm to clap Shemsen on the shoulder. 灰胡子腾出一只手，拍了拍舍姆森的肩。 4. Sometimes people will clap wildly after you dance. 有时候，你跳完舞后人们会疯狂地鼓掌。 5. There was a clap of thunder in the distance. 远处有雷鸣。', '过去式: clapped 过去分词: clapped 现在分词: clapping 第三人称单数: claps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accelerate', '[ək\'seləreɪt]', 'v.加速；提前；跳级', '1. Our present task is to accelerate economic growth. 加速经济发展是我们当前的任务。 2. The leader is losing ground as the rest of the runners accelerate. 领先者在其余赛跑者加速时就逐渐失去了优势。 3. We will accelerate the reform of the financial system under these circumstances. 在这一背景情况下,我们将加快金融体制改革。 4. The decline of her health seemed to suddenly accelerate. 她的健康状况好像突然提前衰退了。', '形容词: accelerative 过去式: accelerated 过去分词: accelerated 现在分词: accelerating 第三人称单数: accelerates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('explain', '[ɪk\'spleɪn]', 'v.说明；解释', '1. She explained her conduct to her boss. 她向老板说明了自己那种表现的原因。 2. He explained his plan in some detail. 他仔细地说明了自己的计划。 3. The lawyer explained the new law to us. 律师向我们解释了新法律。', '形容词: explainable 过去式: explained 过去分词: explained 现在分词: explaining 第三人称单数: explains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rather', '[\'ræðər]', 'adv.相当；宁愿；有点儿 int.<英口> 好呀', '1. Poultry is rather cheap now. 现在的禽肉相当便宜。 2. I would rather stay at home. 我宁可呆在家里。 3. I would rather fail than cheat in the examination. 我宁愿考不及格，也不愿意考试作弊。 4. These shoes are rather too big. 这双鞋有点太大了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pasture', '[\'pæstʃər]', 'n.牧场；草原 vi.吃草 vt.放牧', '1. The land was used chiefly for pasture. 这土地多半用作牧场。 2. We have put our cattle out to pasture. 我们已经把牛放到牧场上吃草去了。 3. Cows are grazing in the pasture. 牛正在草原吃草。 4. Draping the skin over his shoulders, he went to the pasture to wait for the lion. 把羊皮披在身上后，猎人到草原上去等狮子。 5. There we saw herds of cows grazing on the pasture. 我们在那里看到一群群的牛在草地上吃草。 6. Cows are left to graze in the pasture. 奶牛都是留给放牧在牧场。', '形容词: pasturable 名词: pasturer 过去式: pastured 过去分词: pastured 现在分词: pasturing 第三人称单数: pastures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('TRUE', '[truː]', 'adj.真实的；真的；准确的；精确的；忠诚的 adv.真实地；准确地 n.真相；精确 vt.使...平衡', '1. She gave the true account of what had happened. 她如实地讲述了发生的事情。 2. On what grounds do you say that is true? 你根据什么说那是真的? 3. We both thought that he had given a true judgement. 我们都认为他给出了正确的判断。 4. He was true to his word. 他信守诺言。 5. She spoke truer than she knew. 她说的比她了解的更接近事实。 6. Two of the pictures hanging on the wall are out of true. 挂在墙上的照片中有两张挂得不正。 7. It is not easy to true up a frame. 做个标准的框架也不容易。', '比较级: truer 最高级: truest 名词: trueness 过去式: trued 过去分词: trued 现在分词: truing/trueing 第三人称单数: trues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cooperative', '[koʊ\'ɑːpərətɪv]', 'adj.合作的；协作的 n.合作社', '1. We found him friendly and cooperative. 我们感到他是友好的，乐于合作的。 2. They are trying to adopt a more cooperative posture. 他们正试图采取更为合作的态度。 3. The management would like to thank the staff for being so cooperative. 资方要感谢全体员工的通力合作。 4. The school was very cooperative when we made a film there. 我们到该校拍摄影片时，获得校方的大力协助。 5. They decided to set up a cooperative. 他们决定开办一家合作社。', '副词: cooperatively 名词: cooperativeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('establish', '[ɪ\'stæblɪʃ]', 'v.建立；确立；创办；安顿', '1. We have established trade ties with these regions. 我们和这些地区建立了贸易关系。 2. There is an urgent need to establish a strict responsibility system. 急需建立严格的责任制度。 3. He has established his theory. 他确立了他的学说。 4. The framework of a social security system was established by and large. 社会保障体系框架基本确立。', '名词: establisher 过去式: established 过去分词: established 现在分词: establishing 第三人称单数: establishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chess', '[tʃes]', 'n.国际象棋', '1. My win at chess raised my spirits a little. 我赢了这盘国际象棋才打起了一点精神。 2. I\'m not very fond of playing chess. 我不太喜欢下棋。 3. It was the first time I\'d won since I\'d learnt to play chess. 自从我学会下国际象棋以来，这是我第一次赢。 4. Chess is his favorite diversion. 象棋是他最喜欢的娱乐活动。', '名词复数: chess');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('everyday', '[\'evrideɪ]', 'adj.日常的；平常的', '1. Using the tips below, you can make thankfulness an everyday habit. 看一看以下的建议吧，你会把感恩变成日常的习惯。 2. Slowly insidiously the fog of the everyday has returned to enshroud me. 慢慢地，不知不觉地，日常的迷雾又回来笼罩了我。 3. In a bizarre profession anything which belongs to an everyday routine gains great values. 从事不寻常职业的人，日常生活中任何一件极平常的事物对他都具有不平凡的价值。 4. He is in his everyday clothes. 他穿着平常的衣服。', '名词: everydayness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('offend', '[ə\'fend]', 'vt.冒犯；犯罪 vi.违反；令人不适', '1. I didn\'t mean to offend you. 我不是故意冒犯你。 2. We were careful not to offend his nibs. 我们小心翼翼不敢冒犯这位要人。 3. You would be wise enough not to offend him. 你最好是不去冒犯他。 4. He did not offend against the law . 他没犯法。 5. We mustn\'t offend against their customs. 我们不能违反他们的风俗。', '过去式: offended 过去分词: offended 现在分词: offending 第三人称单数: offends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cheek', '[tʃiːk]', 'n.面颊；脸蛋', '1. A bullet grazed his cheek. 子弹擦伤了他的面颊。 2. She has a tiny mole on her cheek. 她面颊上有一颗小痣。 3. Philip stroked the baby\'s little cheek. 菲利浦摸着那婴儿的小脸蛋。 4. Rosie gave her an affectionate kiss on each cheek. 罗西在她的脸蛋上每边亲昵地吻了一下。', '过去式: cheeked 过去分词: cheeked 现在分词: cheeking 第三人称单数: cheeks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evaluate', '[ɪ\'væljueɪt]', 'vt.评价；评估', '1. Let\'s evaluate the evidence. 让我们评定一下此证据的价值。 2. The school has only been open for six months, so it\'s too early to evaluate its success. 这所学校开办还不过六个月，所以要对它的成绩作出评价为时尚早。 3. Enterprise should acquaint with its storage status, that\'s the reason why it needs to evaluate the storage material. 企业应对自身库存状况有清楚的了解,这就需要对各个物资做出评价。 4. At the conclusion of the test run, evaluate the test results. 在测试完成之后,对测试的结果进行评估;', '形容词: evaluative 名词: evaluation 过去式: evaluated 过去分词: evaluated 现在分词: evaluating 第三人称单数: evaluates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rape', '[reɪp]', 'n.强奸；蹂躏；破坏 v.强奸；掠夺；蹂躏', '1. She showed a prurient interest in the details of the rape case. 她对那强奸案的细节津津乐道。 2. There is mention of capital penalties for rape. 对强奸有死刑的规定。 3. Their action led to the rape of the countryside. 他们的行为破坏了乡村。 4. He attempts to rape the heroine. 他想去强奸女主人公。', '名词: raper 过去式: raped 过去分词: raped 现在分词: raping 第三人称单数: rapes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disgrace', '[dɪs\'ɡreɪs]', 'n.耻辱 v.耻辱；丢脸', '1. The dirty classrooms are a disgrace to the school. 肮脏的教室是学校的耻辱。 2. Her actions brought disgrace on his family. 她的行为给她的家庭带来了耻辱。 3. You will bring disgrace on yourself by doing this. 你这样做会给自己带来耻辱。 4. He quit in disgrace over the bribe. 他因受贿而不光彩地辞职了。 5. He will die before he shall disgrace himself. 他宁肯死而决不受侮辱。', '名词: disgracer 过去式: disgraced 过去分词: disgraced 现在分词: disgracing 第三人称单数: disgraces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bearing', '[\'berɪŋ]', 'n.轴承；举止；忍受；支撑物；影响', '1. These non-contact seals do not limit bearing speed. 这些非无接触式密封件不限制轴承转速。 2. Shanghai HRB bearing Supplies Company Ltd. 上海哈轴轴承配套有限公司。 3. Her dignified bearing throughout the trial made everyone believe she was innocent. 在整个审讯的过程中，她那端庄的举止使得每个人都相信她是无辜的。 4. The pain was almost past bearing. 疼痛几乎无法忍受。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('designate', '[\'dezɪɡneɪt]', 'vt.指定；标明；把...定名为；选派 adj.指定的', '1. She was designated sportswoman of the year. 她被指定为本年度的体坛明星。 2. The chairman has designated that boy as his successor. 主席已经指定那个男孩作他的继承人。 3. Black lines designate boundaries on this map. 在这幅地图上黑线标示疆界。 4. The ruler of a kingdom is designated a king. 王国的统治者称作国王。 5. The ambassador designate is going to meet honored foreign guests. 大使指定人选将要迎接外国贵客。', '形容词: designative 名词: designator 过去式: designated 过去分词: designated 现在分词: designating 第三人称单数: designates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appraisal', '[ə\'preɪzl]', 'n.估计；评估', '1. All events have proved our appraisal to be correct. 一切事实都证明，我们估计得正确。 2. The judge made a cold appraisal of the evidence. 法官对这一证据作了一番毫无偏见的估计。 3. She gave us a realistic appraisal of our chances. 她对我们的机会做了一个现实的评估 4. His appraisal of the novel is appropriate. 他对这部小说的评价非常得当。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('petrol', '[\'petrəl]', 'n.<英>汽油', '1. Petrol is volatile. 汽油容易挥发。 2. The petrol is running out. 汽油快要耗尽了。 3. My car is rather heavy on petrol. 我的汽车很费油。 4. They have increased the price of petrol again. 他们又提高了汽油的价格。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spelling', '[\'spelɪŋ]', 'n.拼法；拼写', '1. Don\'t make a mistake in your spelling. 不要在拼法上出错。 2. English spelling has little rhyme or reason. 英文的拼法没什么规律。 3. He is certainly improving in his spelling. 他的拼写大有改进。 4. The composition is not well written, and moreover, there are many spelling mistakes in it. 这篇作文写得不好，而且还有许多拼写错误。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('me', '[mi:]', 'pron.我(宾格)', '1. Let me see. 让我想一想。 2. They paid me the princely sum of USD5000. 他们慷慨地给我5000美元。 3. Give it to me. 把它给我！ 4. He asked me if I would go fishing with him tomorrow. 他问我明天是否和他一起去钓鱼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('learn', '[lɜːrn]', 'v.学会；学习；得知', '1. Write out this word ten times so that you learn how to spell it. 把这个字抄写十遍就能记住怎麽拼写了。 2. It\'s more useful to learn modern languages, such as English and German, than Latin. 学习英语和德语等现代语言比学习拉丁语更为有用。 3. I\'m trying to learn English. 我正在尽力学英语。 4. I learned this news from the newspaper. 我从报纸上得知这个消息。', '形容词: learnable 名词: learner 过去式: learned/learnt 过去分词: learned/learnt 现在分词: learning 第三人称单数: learns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trail', '[treɪl]', 'n.踪迹；小径；尾；一系列 vi.拖；落后于 vt.追踪；拖拽；尾随', '1. The dogs found the trail of the rabbit. 猎狗发现了兔子的踪迹。 2. I am going to meet him at the end of the trail. 我会在小路的尽头跟他见面。 3. The carriage left a trail of dust. 马车后扬起了一缕烟尘。 4. The wounded animal left a trail of blood behind it. 受伤的动物在身后留下一道血迹。 5. The bride\'s long skirt trailed along behind her. 新娘的长裙拖在身后。 6. He trailed the beast to its lair. 他追猎野兽到兽穴。', '过去式: trailed 过去分词: trailed 现在分词: trailing 第三人称单数: trails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('infrared', '[ˌɪnfrə\'red]', 'adj.红外线的 n.红外线', '1. Infrared cameras can also make false positives. 红外线摄影机也会判断错误。 2. The bathroom could be warmed by an infrared lamp. 可以使用红外线灯来温暖那间浴室。 3. The gunsight has an infrared lens for night vision. 射击瞄准器装有用于夜间视力的红外线镜头。 4. What are infrared and ultraviolet rays? 什么是红外线和紫外线？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obligation', '[ˌɑːblɪ\'ɡeɪʃn]', 'n.义务；责任', '1. We are invited, but we are under no obligation to go. 我们是被邀请了,但并不意味着我们有义务一定要去。 2. Some people suggest that the old people\'s children have the obligation to look after their old parents. 一些人认为：老年人的子女有义务照看他们的父母。 3. I have an obligation to keep secret for the taxpayer. 我有责任为纳税人保密。', '形容词: obligational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reluctant', '[rɪ\'lʌktənt]', 'adj.不情愿的；勉强的', '1. They were very reluctant to help. 他们不大愿意帮忙。 2. I was reluctant to do over the stitching in the dress. 我不愿意把衣服上的线脚拆了重缝。 3. By 1982 they had become reluctant to extend new loans to public borrowers. 到1982年，他们已不愿向公共借贷者发放新的贷款。 4. Margaret gave him a reluctant consent. 玛格丽特勉强答应了他。', '副词: reluctantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hinder', '[\'hɪndər]', 'v.阻碍；打扰 adj.后面的', '1. The crowd hindered him from leaving. 人群使他无法脱身。 2. Heavy snow hindered the construction work. 大雪妨碍了这项建筑工程的进行。 3. Don\'t let me hinder you from going. 别让我妨碍了你走。 4. Don\'t hinder me. 不要妨碍我。 5. The hinder leg of this horse was broken. 这匹马的后腿断了。', '名词: hinderer 过去式: hindered 过去分词: hindered 现在分词: hindering 第三人称单数: hinders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dive', '[daɪv]', 'n.潜水；跳水 vi.跳水；俯冲；潜心钻研', '1. Our dive is a part of this expedition. 我们这次潜水活动就是属于这个远航的一部分。 2. What a beautiful dive! 多么优美的跳水！ 3. He dived from the bridge and rescued the drowning child. 他从桥上跳入水中，救起溺水的孩子。 4. The eagle dived down on the rabbit. 那只鹰向兔子猛扑下来。', '过去式: dived/dove 过去分词: dived 现在分词: diving 第三人称单数: dives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eternal', '[ɪ\'tɜːrnl]', 'adj.永久的；永恒的 n.永恒的事', '1. The price of liberty is eternal vigilance. 自由的代价是永久提高警惕。 2. The bad man will suffer eternal damnation. 坏人将会受到永远的惩罚。 3. He is, as it were, an eternal boy. 他好像是个永远年轻的小伙子。 4. She felt eternal gratitude to him for saving her life. 她终生感激他的救命之恩。 5. The eternal motion of the stars fascinated him. 星体永恒的运行使他著迷。', '副词: eternally 名词: eternality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ice-cream', '[\'aɪskriːm]', 'n.冰淇淋', '1. The boys were regaling on ice cream cones. 男孩们在美滋滋地大吃冰淇淋。 2. Mother knows how to make ice cream. 母亲会做冰淇淋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('condense', '[kən\'dens]', 'v.浓缩；凝结；缩短', '1. He condense his speech to half its original length. 他把演讲的长度浓缩了一半。 2. You can condense milk by boiling away much of the water in it. 煮去牛奶中大部分的水分可使它浓缩。 3. Steam condenses into water when cooling down. 蒸汽冷却时凝结成水。 4. Water vapors can condense to form clouds. 水蒸汽能凝结成云。', '形容词: condensable 名词: condensability 过去式: condensed 过去分词: condensed 现在分词: condensing 第三人称单数: condenses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('navigation', '[ˌnævɪ\'ɡeɪʃn]', 'n.导航；航行；航海', '1. Mechanics discovered problems with the plane\'s navigation system. 机械工发现飞机的导航系统存在问题。 2. Navigation is difficult on this river because of the hide rock. 因为有暗礁，在这条河上航行很困难。 3. The compass is an instrument of navigation. 罗盘是航行仪器。 4. The canal has been opened up to steam navigation. 运河已经可以航行轮船。', '形容词: navigational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('siren', '[\'saɪrən]', 'n.汽笛；警报器 n.[希神]塞壬（半鸟半女人的怪物）；妖妇；迷人的女人', '1. He made out of the cabin at once on hearing the siren. 他一听到汽笛声就立即走出船舱。 2. The wails of the siren woke the people out of their dreams. 汽笛的啸鸣把人们从睡梦中惊醒。 3. The siren went off at noon. 警笛在正午鸣响 4. We all heard the air-raid siren. 我们都听到了空袭警报器的声音。 5. Who can resist your temptation like a siren. 有谁能抗拒你那份像塞壬一样的诱惑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('portable', '[\'pɔːrtəbl]', 'adj.轻便的；手提式的；[计]可移植的 n.便携的东西', '1. The portable device easily knocks down. 这种轻便装置容易拆卸。 2. Portable telephones are very popular nowadays. 现今，移动电话非常普及。 3. She traded her roller-skates for Billy\'s portable radio. 她拿旱冰鞋换了比利的手提收音机。 4. The new portable computers are going like hot cakes. 新的便携式计算机卖得很快。', '副词: portably 名词: portability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('increase', '[ɪn\'kriːs]', 'v.增加；提高 n.增加；增强；提高', '1. We anticipate that demand is likely to increase. 我们预料需求可能增加。 2. Wide reading will increase your vocabulary. 博览群书会增加你的词汇量。 3. They have increased the price of petrol again. 他们又提高了汽油的价格。 4. We must increase our output to meet demand. 我们必须提高产量满足需求。 5. There was a steady increase in population. 人口在不断增长中。', '形容词: increasable 副词: increasingly 名词: increaser 过去式: increased 过去分词: increased 现在分词: increasing 第三人称单数: increases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('or', '[ɔːr]', 'conj.或者；还是；否则 prep.<古>在...之前', '1. You can send letters by mail or by hand. 你可以邮寄或者派人送信件。 2. Is that painting an original or a reproduction? 那幅画是原作还是复制品？ 3. Which do you prefer, lamb chops or pork chops? 你比较喜欢小羊排,还是猪排? 4. Hurry up or else you\'ll be late. 快，否则你就要来不及了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('future', '[\'fjuːtʃər]', 'adj.将来的 n.将来；前程；期货', '1. Take no thought for your future needs. 不必为将来的需要而操心。 2. Do you really care nothing about your future? 你真的一点也不关心你的将来？ 3. He felt at ease and confident about the future. 他对未来感到轻松自在并且充满信心。 4. We will meet in Beijing in the near future. 在不久的将来，我们将在北京见面。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fair', '[fer]', 'adj.公平的；晴朗的；美丽的; 相当的；（皮肤、毛发等）浅色的；白皙的 n.展览会；市集 adv.公平地，直接地', '1. He won the game fair and square. 他赢得这次比赛是公平的。 2. Soames said that he was not getting a fair go. 索米斯说他没有得到公平的对待。 3. The rainbow promises fair weather. 虹预示晴朗的天气。 4. A foul morning may turn to a fair day. 天气不好的早晨能变成晴朗的白天。 5. The visitors spied the exhibits at the fair. 参观者细细察看展览会上的陈列品。', '比较级: fairer 最高级: fairest 名词: fairness 过去式: faired 过去分词: faired 现在分词: fairing 第三人称单数: fairs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('concern', '[kən\'sɜːrn]', 'n.关心；关心的事；忧虑，担心 vt.涉及；影响；关心；（使）担心 n.公司；企业', '1. Hardly a whisper of concern has been voiced. 没有人表示过一点点的关心。 2. Provision of shelter was their main concern for the disaster victims. 为灾民提供避难处是他们最关切的事。 3. I am not insensible of your concern. 我不是没察觉到你的忧虑。 4. The theory of relativity is concerned with two seemingly opposite ideas. 相对论涉及两个似乎对应的概念。 5. Rarely would a single concern have the entire facilities required for a complete testing program. 很少有一个公司能拥有为完成整个试验大纲所需要的全部设备。', '过去式: concerned 过去分词: concerned 现在分词: concerning 第三人称单数: concerns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('torch', '[tɔːrtʃ]', 'n.手电筒；火炬；火把；<俚>纵火犯 v.纵火', '1. He turned on the torch to look for his keys. 他打开了手电筒，寻找钥匙。 2. Shine your torch into the drawer. 你用手电筒照一下这抽屉里面。 3. The torch flared in the darkness. 火炬在黑暗中闪光。 4. His emblems are the spear and the burning torch. 他佩带的徽记是长矛和燃烧着的火炬。 5. The rioters began to torch the buildings. 暴民开始放火烧楼。', '过去式: torched 过去分词: torched 现在分词: torching 第三人称单数: torches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('court', '[kɔːrt]', 'n.法院；庭院；宫廷；球场；奉承 v.献殷勤；追求；招致；设法获得', '1. Sherman recommended that Clarke be disciplined, but higher-ups rejected the idea. 谢尔曼建议对克拉克进行纪律惩戒，但高层拒绝了这个意见。 2. My court is deserted but I do not care. 我的庭院一片荒芜但是我无心照看。 3. The court of King Solomon was noted for its splendor. 所罗门国王的宫廷以其华丽著称。 4. The court moves to the country in the summer. 夏天王室上下都移居到乡下去。 5. He has been courting the director, hoping to get the leading role in the play. 他一直在讨好导演，想在剧中扮演主角。', '过去式: courted 过去分词: courted 现在分词: courting 第三人称单数: courts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('humiliate', '[hjuː\'mɪlieɪt]', 'vt.使 ... 蒙羞；使丢脸', '1. She was humiliated because her children behaved so badly. 她为她的孩子表现不好而感到羞辱。 2. Though I aim to defeat you, should I succeed, I will not humiliate you. 虽然我的目标是战胜你,但就算我胜利了,那并不会让你蒙羞。 3. The boy humiliate his parents by behaving badly in front of the guests. 那男孩在客人面前表现不好,使父母丢面子。 4. I didn\'t want to humiliate her in front of her colleagues. 我不想当着她同事们的面令她难堪。', '过去式: humiliated 过去分词: humiliated 现在分词: humiliating 第三人称单数: humiliates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mug', '[mʌɡ]', 'n.脸；杯；一杯的量；恶棍 v.打劫；突击学习', '1. caught a glimpse of his ugly mug; 瞥见他的丑脸； 2. Wear a straw hat and bring a mug with you. 你要戴上草帽，带上杯子。 3. This mug has a chip in it. 这个缸子上有个缺口。 4. He has a mug of cocoa before bed. 他临睡前喝一缸子可可。 5. I was walking out to my car when a man tried to mug me. 我正朝汽车走去,突然有人试图抢劫我。', '过去式: mugged 过去分词: mugged 现在分词: mugging 第三人称单数: mugs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('belly', '[\'beli]', 'n.腹部 v.膨胀', '1. My belly is empty. 我肚子饿了。 2. A hungry belly has no ears. 人肚子饿了就听不进道理。 3. The robber stabbed the young man in the belly. 强盗刺伤了这名年轻人的腹部。 4. The boat carried with much cargo in its belly. 该船的舱里载了很多的货物。 5. The sails bellied in the wind. 帆在风中鼓得满满的。', '名词复数: bellies 过去式: bellied 过去分词: bellied 现在分词: bellying 第三人称单数: bellies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whose', '[huːz]', 'pron.谁的 adj.谁的', '1. No one knows whose dictionary this is. 无人知道这是谁的字典。 2. Whose life have you touched today? 今天你会走进谁的生活？ 3. No one knows whose dictionary this is. 无人知道这是谁的字典。 4. Whose life have you touched today? 今天你会走进谁的生活？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shark', '[ʃɑːrk]', 'n.鲨鱼 n.贪婪的人；放高利贷的人；老手 v.诈取；诈骗', '1. The shark snapped its jaws shut. 鲨鱼啪嗒一声把嘴合上了。 2. The shark is dangerous to swimmers. 鲨鱼对游泳的人来说很危险。 3. He told me he once caught a shark, but I know he was swinging the lead. 他告诉我有一回他捕到了一条鲨鱼，我知道他是在胡诌。 4. That shark lent me money at very high interest rate. 那个贪婪狡猾的人以很高的利率借给我钱。', '过去式: sharked 过去分词: sharked 现在分词: sharking 第三人称单数: sharks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lab', '[læb]', 'n.<口>实验室；拉布拉多猎犬', '1. I\'ll meet you outside the science lab. 我在科学实验室外面见你。 2. Charlie the black lab drove his owner\'s car into the Pend Oreille River. 黑拉布拉多犬查理把主人的车开入庞多雷河。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sail', '[seɪl]', 'v.航行；驾(船) n.帆；航行；航海', '1. This ship sails for New York on Monday. 这船将于星期一开往纽约。 2. The ship was given the all-clear to sail again. 这艘船得到恢复航行的许可。 3. Can you sail a boat? 你会驾驶船只吗？ 4. The sailors heaved at rope to tighten the sail. 水手们用力拉绳把帆绷紧。', '过去式: sailed 过去分词: sailed 现在分词: sailing 第三人称单数: sails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('footstep', '[\'fʊtstep]', 'n.脚步；脚步声；足迹', '1. The store is just a footstep away. 那家店仅一步之遥。 2. I heard his footsteps in the hall. 我听见大厅里有他的脚步声。 3. There are many footsteps in the snow. 雪地上有许多脚印。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('immediate', '[ɪ\'miːdiət]', 'adj.直接的；最接近的；立即的；目前的', '1. The immediate cause of death is unknown. 造成死亡的直接原因不明。 2. He seldom expected to receive any immediate profit. 他倒不一定是想从中捞到什么直接的好处。 3. The evidence has no immediate bearing on the case. 该证据与本案无直接关系。 4. His immediate successors fell into the same trap. 他的直接继承者也堕入了这一陷阱。', '名词: immediateness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pin', '[pɪn]', 'n.别针（大头针）；徽章；<口>脚 v.钉住；别住；固定住 abbr.个人识别码（=Personal Identification Number）,<印>邮编（=Postal Index Number）', '1. I bought a tie pin for my husband yesterday. 昨天我给丈夫买了一支领带别针。 2. He pinned the notice to the board. 他把通知钉在布告牌上。 3. Pin the bills together so you don\'t lose them. 把账单别在一起以防遗失。 4. The general pinned the medal on the soldier\'s chest. 将军把奖章别在这位士兵的胸前。', '过去式: pinned 过去分词: pinned 现在分词: pinning 第三人称单数: pins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('base', '[beɪs]', 'n.底部；基地；基础；基数；基线；(棒球)垒；[化]碱 vt.以 ... 作基础 adj.卑鄙的；不道德的', '1. I found a small leaf at the base of the flower. 我在那朵花的底部发现一片小叶。 2. Our mission was over, and went back to our base. 我们的任务结束了,我们返回了基地。 3. Many languages have Latin as their base. 许多语言都以拉丁语为基础。 4. One billion new consumers will double the existing consumer base within the next decade. 未来10年内全球将新增10亿消费者,消费者基数将较现在增加一倍。 5. This novel is based on historical facts. 这部小说是以历史事实为根据的。 6. To betray a friend is a base action. 背叛朋友是卑劣的行为。', '副词: basely 比较级: baser 最高级: basest 过去式: based 过去分词: based 现在分词: basing 第三人称单数: bases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inhabit', '[ɪn\'hæbɪt]', 'v.居住于；占据；栖息', '1. Broadly, we investigate the world\'s lakes and rivers and the creatures which inhabit them. 宽广地，我们调查世界的湖和河和居住于他们的人。 2. Wookiees inhabit the upper levels of the forest, having built their massive cities within the interwoven canopy. 伍基人占据了树林的上层，并在交织的树冠上建造了巨大的城市。 3. Under Forman\'s tutelage, actors fully inhabit their roles, the hospital becomes an evil institution, and the movie poignantly celebrates the human spirit. 根据福尔曼的指导，演员完全占据自己的角色，医院成为一个邪恶的机构，和电影尖锐地庆祝人类的精神。 4. Many types of seabirds inhabit the coral island. 这个珊瑚岛上栖息着很多种海鸟。', '形容词: inhabitable 名词: inhabitability 过去式: inhabited 过去分词: inhabited 现在分词: inhabiting 第三人称单数: inhabits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('immigrant', '[\'ɪmɪɡrənt]', 'n.移民；侨民', '1. He admitted that he was an illegal immigrant. 他承认他是非法移民。 2. California has many immigrants from other states. 加利福尼亚有许多来自其他州的移民。 3. Immigrant workers were classed as aliens. 移民来的工人已归入侨民类。 4. His father is of native Indian extraction and his mother an immigrant Italian. 他父亲有印第安土著血统，母亲是意大利侨民。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plot', '[plɑːt]', 'n.情节；阴谋；图；(小块)土地 v.密谋；绘图；计划；标示位置', '1. The plot thickens. 情节复杂起来了。 2. They are brewing a plot behind the scenes. 他们正在幕后策划一个阴谋。 3. The silly ending robs the plot of any credibility. 这愚蠢的结尾使得整个情节变得一点都不可信。 4. The reporter was killed because he tried to expose a plot. 这名记者因为试图揭露一个阴谋而被杀害。 5. They are plotting how to murder him. 他们在密谋如何杀害他。', '名词: plotlessness 过去式: plotted 过去分词: plotted 现在分词: plotting 第三人称单数: plots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oral', '[\'ɔːrəl]', 'adj.口头的；口部的；口语的 n.口试', '1. The old man told us a story passed on by oral tradition. 老人给我们讲述了一个口头流传的故事。 2. We hurried an oral agreement before signing a formal contract. 在签正式合同之前，我们先草签了一份口头协议。 3. He gave us an oral report after inspecting the factory. 视察了那家工厂后,他给我们作了口头汇报。 4. Enteric viruses are able to enter in the body via the oral route. 肠道病毒是经口进入人体的。 5. He failed the oral. 他口试不及格。', '副词: orally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scientific', '[ˌsaɪən\'tɪfɪk]', 'adj.科学的', '1. We all support his scientific research. 我们都支持他的科学研究。 2. He took a very scientific approach to management. 他采取了一种非常科学的管理方法。 3. He is engaged in scientific pursuit. 他从事科学研究。', '副词: scientifically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('profit', '[\'prɑːfɪt]', 'n.利润；收益；利益 vi.得益；获利 vt.有益于', '1. There is very little profit in selling newspapers at present. 现在卖报纸利润很少。 2. I want to know the net profit. 我想知道净收益。 3. It is well known that fake and inferior commodities do harm to the profit of consumers. 众所周知,假冒伪劣商品损害了消费者的利益。 4. We profit from the work of the specialist. 我们从专家的工作中得到益处。 5. All his wealth did not profit him. 他所有的财富于他无益。', '形容词: profitless 过去式: profited 过去分词: profited 现在分词: profiting 第三人称单数: profits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('release', '[rɪ\'liːs]', 'n.释放；让渡；发行 vt.释放；让与；准予发表；发射', '1. The prisoner was questioned before his release. 囚犯被释放之前受到了审问。 2. The puffball is ready to release its spores. 尘菌已经要释放孢子了。 3. The electrons in the upper band eventually release energy, thereby emitting photons. 上层能带中的电子最后会发射光子释放能量。', '过去式: released 过去分词: released 现在分词: releasing 第三人称单数: releases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chamber', '[\'tʃeɪmbər]', 'n.室；会议厅；房间 adj.【音】室内的，小型的；私人的，秘密的', '1. The heart has four chambers. 心脏有两房两室。 2. Most of the meetings are held in the council chamber of city hall. 大多数的会议都在市政大厅的理事会议室举行。 3. The judge met the two lawyers in his chamber. 法官在他的办公室里会见了两位律师。', '过去式: chambered 过去分词: chambered 现在分词: chambering 第三人称单数: chambers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('owe', '[oʊ]', 'vt.欠（债；钱；人情等）；应当给予；感激；把...归功于', '1. I gotta get back there, I owe it to them. 我要回到那,我欠他们的。 2. Incidentally, I think you still owe me some money. 顺便说一句, 我想你还欠我一些钱。 3. I owe you one. 我欠你一个人情。 4. You owe yourself a holiday. 你应该给自己安排个假期。', '过去式: owed 过去分词: owed 现在分词: owing 第三人称单数: owes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('send', '[send]', 'vt.发送；派遣；使处于...的状态；放出；运输 vi.差遣；发出；传送', '1. You are now ready to send messages. 现在你可以可以发送消息了。 2. Radio Beijing sends the news all over the world. 北京广播电台向全世界播送新闻。 3. I\'ll send someone to show you around. 我派人带你到周围转转。 4. The music of this song sent her carefree and joyous. 这支歌的乐曲使她心旷神怡。 5. I think we need to send out for the missing lamb. 我想我们得派个人去找那头迷路的小羊羔。', '名词: sender 过去式: sent 过去分词: sent 现在分词: sending 第三人称单数: sends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mere', '[mɪr]', 'adj.仅仅的；纯粹的', '1. Don\'t scold him, he is a mere child. 别责备他,他只不过是个孩子。 2. Her liberal views were soon revealed as mere posturing. 她那些开明的观点很快地就暴露出只不过是做做样子而已。 3. The peasant laboured for a mere pittance. 农民仅仅是为了微不足道的收入而辛苦地劳作。 4. A mere child cannot do the work of a man. 仅仅是个孩子是不能做成人工作的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tendency', '[\'tendənsi]', 'n.趋势；倾向；秉性', '1. There is a tendency towards regional cooperation. 有一种地区性合作的趋势。 2. There is a growing tendency for people to work at home instead of in offices. 人们在家里而不是在办公室里工作的趋势日益增长。 3. Today there is a tendency for people to opt out of social activity. 现在,越来越多的人倾向于不参加社会活动。 4. They tried to stop the tendency of inflation. 他们设法阻止住了通货膨胀的势头。', '名词复数: tendencies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trend', '[trend]', 'n.趋势；倾向；方位 vi.倾向；转向', '1. The trend of prices is still upward. 物价仍有上涨趋势。 2. The youth like to follow the latest trends in fashion. 年轻人喜好追求最新的流行款式。 3. This quartet represents a major new trend in modern music. 这首四重奏的曲子反映了现代音乐中一种主要的新趋向。 4. The event changed the trend of public opinion. 这件事改变了舆论的趋向。 5. The prices of houses are trending upwards. 房价趋于上涨。', '过去式: trended 过去分词: trended 现在分词: trending 第三人称单数: trends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('purpose', '[\'pɜːrpəs]', 'n.目的；决心；意图；议题 v.打算；决意', '1. What is the purpose of your visit? 你来访的目的是什么？ 2. He was a man of purpose. 他是一个意志坚强的人 3. I am sure that he came here with ill purpose. 我敢断定,他这次来意图不轨。 4. What is the purpose of this meeting? 这次会议的议题是什么？ 5. He purposed to visit South America. 他计划去南美。', '过去式: purposed 过去分词: purposed 现在分词: purposing 第三人称单数: purposes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('holy', '[\'hoʊli]', 'adj.神圣的；圣洁的；令人敬仰的', '1. To the children, their father\'s study was the holy of holies. 在这些孩子的眼里，父亲的书房是最神圣的地方。 2. Jerusalem was regarded as the holy place by the Christians. 耶路撒冷被基督徒们认为是圣地。 3. They led a holy life. 他们过着圣洁的生活。 4. The poem sings the praises of holy love. 这首诗歌颂圣洁的爱。', '副词: holily 比较级: holier 最高级: holiest 名词: holiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fish', '[fɪʃ]', 'n.鱼；鱼肉；笨蛋；新手；新囚犯 v.钓鱼；捕鱼；摸索；搜寻', '1. We caught three little fishes. 我们捉到三条小鱼。 2. The fish plopped back into the river. 那鱼扑通一声跃回河中。 3. There is much fish on the plate. 盘子里有不少鱼肉。 4. Meat and fish are often kept in cold storage. 鱼肉常存放在冷藏库中。 5. The beach is a good place to fish from. 海滩是钓鱼的好地方。', '名词复数: fish 过去式: fished 过去分词: fished 现在分词: fishing 第三人称单数: fishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reign', '[reɪn]', 'n.君主统治；在位期 v.统治；支配', '1. He has a tyrannical reign on his empire. 他是个残暴的皇帝。 2. People will remember the tyrannies of his reign. 人们不会忘记他统治时期的暴行。 3. The reign of Queen Victoria lasted more than sixty years. 维多利亚女王的统治持续了六十多年。 4. The American Revolution took place during the reign of George III. 美国独立战争发生在英王乔治三世统治时期。 5. He reigned over the country for forty years. 他统治了这个国家四十年。', '过去式: reigned 过去分词: reigned 现在分词: reigning 第三人称单数: reigns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('subsidy', '[\'sʌbsədi]', 'n.津贴；补助金', '1. It\'s the old and the poor who suffer worst when subsidies are cut. 补助津贴一削减，最吃苦头的就是那些老人和贫民。 2. She qualifies for the unemployment subsidy . 她有权获得失业补贴。 3. The townsfolk can\'t understand why the Royal Shakespeare Company needs a subsidy. 市民不明白王室莎士比亚公司为什么需要一个补助金。', '名词复数: subsidies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('speech', '[spiːtʃ]', 'n.演说；演讲；言语；语言能力', '1. The mayor made a speech at the opening. 市长在开幕式上发表了演说。 2. The speaker will soon wind up his speech. 演说者就要结束他的讲话了。 3. I had to give a speech to the press club. 我得向记者俱乐部发表演说。 4. He closed his speech with a funny joke. 他用一则有趣的笑话结束了演讲。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bright', '[braɪt]', 'adj.明亮的；聪明的；阳光的；生动的；有前途的 adv.一早 n.亮色', '1. The bright moonlight showed the Taj Mahal in all its glory. 泰姬陵在明亮的月光下显得光彩夺目。 2. He grew up in the country, but then found he preferred the bright lights. 他在乡村长大，但後来觉得很喜欢繁华的都市生活。 3. He is not bright, but he always works hard. 他并不聪明，但工作总是勤勤恳恳。 4. The class are, in general, very bright. 总的说来, 这个班级的学生都很聪明。 5. We must leave bright and early in the morning. 我们必须一大清早就离开。 6. You look better in bright colors like orange and red. 你穿亮色的衣服感觉更好看，比如橙色和红色就不错。', '副词: brightly 比较级: brighter 最高级: brightest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peach', '[piːtʃ]', 'n.桃子；桃树；桃红色', '1. The peach is a sweet and juicy fruit. 桃子是甜又多汁的水果。 2. The beauty of the peach blossom is beyond description. 桃花的美丽难以形容。 3. There is a peach standing by the lake. 湖边有棵桃树。 4. Peach is the most popular color this season. 桃红色是这一季最受欢迎的颜色。', '过去式: peached 过去分词: peached 现在分词: peaching 第三人称单数: peaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('association', '[əˌsoʊʃi\'eɪʃn]', 'n.协会；社团；交往；联想；联合；结合', '1. Have you joined the teachers\' association? 你加入教师协会了吗? 2. About 20 people have registered in the association. 大约有20人已登记加入这一协会。 3. There is a hide-and-seek association with a leader who is nowhere to be found. 有一个躲猫猫社团，他们的团长现在还没有找到。 4. Horwath refers to Horwath International Association, a Swiss verein. 浩华是指浩华国际协会，为一个根据瑞士法律所组成的社团组织。', '形容词: associational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rice', '[raɪs]', 'n.米；米饭；稻', '1. Rice is our essential foodstuff in life. 大米是我们生活的基本食物。 2. His plate was piled high with rice. 他的盘子里盛满了米饭。 3. He had some rice for supper. 晚饭时他吃了一些米饭。 4. Rice yields will be higher than last year. 稻产量将高于去年。', '过去式: riced 过去分词: riced 现在分词: ricing 第三人称单数: rices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('warrant', '[\'wɔːrənt]', 'n.委任状；凭证；根据；正当理由 vt.担保；保证；辩解；授权', '1. The police obtained a search warrant for his house. 警察拿到了搜查他家的搜查证。 2. Have you got a warrant of fitness for your car? 你有没有一张汽车合格证书? 3. You shouldn\'t arrest him without warrant. 你不能毫无根据地逮捕他。 4. He had no warrant for his suspicion. 他没有理由那么怀疑。 5. I will warrant him an honest and reliable man . 我担保他是个诚实可靠的人。', '形容词: warrantable 副词: warrantably 名词: warrantability 过去式: warranted 过去分词: warranted 现在分词: warranting 第三人称单数: warrants');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thread', '[θred]', 'n.线；思路；螺纹；线索；细丝；帖子 vt.穿过；穿线于；遍布 vi.滴下成丝状；小心地通过；蜿蜒前进', '1. How many spools of thread did you use? 你用了几轴线? 2. The thread seems to match the cloth. 这线和这布似乎很相称。 3. I need one more spool of thread before finishing the embroidery. 再来一轴线我就可以完成这幅刺绣了。 4. He passed me a coil of thread. 他递给我一卷线。', '名词: threader 过去式: threaded 过去分词: threaded 现在分词: threading 第三人称单数: threads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('perish', '[\'perɪʃ]', 'vi.毁灭；消失；腐烂 vt.毁灭；使死亡', '1. We must plan our civilization or we must perish. 我们必须规划我们的文明，否则我们必定毁灭。 2. Almost a hundred people perished in the hotel fire last night. 近百人在昨夜旅馆的大火中丧生。 3. The ancient Aztec culture has all perished now. 古代阿兹台克文化现在已经全部消亡了。 4. Even the best quality rubber will perish with age. 就是最佳质量的橡胶也会因老化而腐烂。 5. Oil on your car tyres will perish them. 在你车胎上的油将会使车胎损坏。', '过去式: perished 过去分词: perished 现在分词: perishing 第三人称单数: perishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('canvas', '[\'kænvəs]', 'n.油画；帆布；（帆布）画布', '1. The artist showed me his canvases. 画家给我看了他的油画。 2. He bought the canvas for ten thousand dollars. 他以一万美元买下这幅油画。 3. The hole was covered (over) with canvas. 这个洞被帆布遮盖住了。 4. The plumber stowed all his gear in a canvas bag. 管子工把他所有的工具都装进一只帆布袋里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('and', '[ənd]', 'conj.和；加；接着；那么', '1. My father and mother went for a walk. 爸爸妈妈去散步了。 2. She majored in maths and physics (at university). 她(在大学)主修数学和物理。 3. She demonstrated that 2 and 2 are four. 她证明2加2等于四。 4. I drove up in front of the house and honked. 我将车开到屋子前面然后按喇叭。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refund', '[\'riːfʌnd]', 'n.偿还；退款 vt.偿还；退还', '1. The residents made a claim for the refund of property tax. 居民们要求发还物业税。 2. We insisted on a refund of the full amount. 我们坚决要求全额退款。 3. Needless to say, we shall refund any expenses you may incur. 不用说，我们将会偿还你所担负的任何费用。 4. We will refund you if the purchase has any quality defect. 如果所购物品存在质量问题，我们将退款给您。', '形容词: refundable 名词: refunder 过去式: refunded 过去分词: refunded 现在分词: refunding 第三人称单数: refunds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sin', '[sɪn]', 'n.原罪 v.犯罪；违反(教规)', '1. He thinks it\'s a sin to covet other\'s properties. 他认为贪图他人的财物是有罪的。 2. I guess ignorance must be a sin. 我认为无知是一种罪。 3. We\'ve sinned against you, and against our fellow men. 我们得罪了你，也得罪了我们的邻人。 4. We are ashamed of sin and yet not ashamed to sin. 我们耻于罪而不耻于犯罪。', '过去式: sinned 过去分词: sinned 现在分词: sinning 第三人称单数: sins 形容词: sinful');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wonderful', '[\'wʌndərfl]', 'adj.精彩的；极好的', '1. Never before have I seen such a wonderful film . 我从未看过如此精彩的影片。 2. Let\'s share the wonderful dolphin show together. 让我们一起欣赏海豚的精彩的表演吧。 3. Rowing is a wonderful water sport. 赛艇是一项精彩的水上运动。 4. All of us were strung highly by his wonderful goal. 我们都为他的精彩进球兴奋不已。', '副词: wonderfully 名词: wonderfulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stall', '[stɔːl]', 'n.栅栏；小隔间；货摊；座位 v.把...关进畜舍里；失速；熄火；拖延；（使）动弹不得', '1. The excited horse flung about in the stall. 受惊的马在马厩里乱冲乱踢。 2. The horse chafed against his stall. 马在厩栏上擦著身子。 3. Our house has a shower stall. 我们房子里有淋浴小隔间。 4. Never buy food from a market stall. 千万别在小摊上买食物。 5. You\'d better stall the pigs. 你最好把猪关在猪圈里饲养。', '过去式: stalled 过去分词: stalled 现在分词: stalling 第三人称单数: stalls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('polite', '[pə\'laɪt]', 'adj.有礼貌的；客气的；有教养的；文雅的', '1. It is not polite of you to cut the speaker short. 你打断发言者的话,真不礼貌。 2. This boy is polite to everyone. 这个男孩对所有人都很礼貌。 3. You may be busy, but you should be polite at least. 你可能很忙,但无论如何你应客气点。 4. Don\'t answer back; it\'s not polite. 不要顶嘴, 这样显得你没教养。', '副词: politely 比较级: politer 最高级: politest 名词: politeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('better', '[\'betər]', 'adj.更好的；较好的 adv.更好地 v.使更好；改善 n.更好者；更优者；下赌注者 形容词good和副词well的比较级形式', '1. Her father transferred her to a better school. 她父亲把她转到了一所更好的学校。 2. The union struck for better work conditions. 工会为争取更好的工作条件而罢工。 3. You must pay extra for a better seat. 如要较好的座位必须另加钱。 4. You would write better if you had a good pen. 要是有枝好笔，就能写得更好。 5. His solution of his debt enabled him to better his daily life. 他还清了债，可以过好点儿的日子了。 6. We had hoped for better. 我们曾希望情况好转。', '过去式: bettered 过去分词: bettered 现在分词: bettering 第三人称单数: betters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deadline', '[\'dedlaɪn]', 'n.最后期限；(鉴于边上的)警戒线；截止时间', '1. I hope we can finish this before the deadline. 我希望我们能在最后期限之前完成这项工作。 2. She was working in haste to meet the deadline. 她匆忙工作是为了赶上最后期限。 3. We pulled out all the stops to meet the deadline. 我们竭尽全力在截止日期前完成了工作。', '过去式: deadlined 过去分词: deadlined 现在分词: deadlining 第三人称单数: deadlines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eligible', '[\'elɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.有资格的；合适的', '1. Mary is not eligible for an award. 玛丽没有申请助学金的资格。 2. Anyone over the age of 18 is eligible to vote. 任何年满18岁的人都有资格投票。 3. I know an eligible young lady who would be an excellent cooperator for you. 我认识一个合适的年青女士,她能成为你最称心如意的合作者。', '副词: eligibly 名词: eligibility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('negotiate', '[nɪ\'ɡoʊʃieɪt]', 'vi.谈判；协商；交涉 vt.谈判达成；成功越过；议价出售', '1. We\'ve decided to negotiate with the employers about our wage claim. 我们决定就工资问题与雇主谈判。 2. We are happy to negotiate with you in that way. 我们很高兴用这种方式来和贵方协商交易。 3. Trade union leaders went back to negotiate with the government. 工会领导回去和政府进行交涉。 4. Since our contract is near its term we must negotiate a new one. 由于我们的合同快到期了，我们必须谈判新的合约。', '形容词: negotiatory 名词: negotiator 过去式: negotiated 过去分词: negotiated 现在分词: negotiating 第三人称单数: negotiates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('what', '[wɑːt]', 'pron.什么 adj.什么；哪个 adv.用于感叹句中 int.什么', '1. What are you having for dinner? 你晚饭吃什么? 2. She is not what she was a few years ago. 她已经不是几年前的她了。 3. What color is your dress? 你的衣服是什么颜色？ 4. What political party does he belong to? 他是哪个政党的成员? 5. What a lovely dog! 狗真可爱呀! 6. What, do you really want to go? 什么！你真的要去？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('could', '[kəd]', 'aux.可以；能；可能；can的过去式', '1. We could relax the procedure slightly in your case. 我们可以根据你的情况通融一些。 2. Could this verb be used in progressive form? 这个动词可以用进行式吗？ 3. I can\'t sing now, but I could when I was young. 现在我不会唱歌了，但我年轻的时候会。 4. The exam results could determine your career. 考试成绩可能会决定你的前途。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('punctual', '[\'pʌŋktʃuəl]', 'adj.准时的；严守时刻的；正点的', '1. My cat makes a punctual appearance at mealtimes. 我的猫一到用餐时间就会准时出现。 2. Please be punctual in futurity. 今后请准时。 3. He likes his guests to be punctual. 他喜欢客人守时。 4. Not being punctual is his greatest shortcoming. 不守时间是他的最大缺点。', '副词: punctually 名词: punctuality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('historical', '[hɪ\'stɔːrɪkl]', 'adj.与历史有关的', '1. People wore historical costumes for the parade. 人们穿著古装参加游行。 2. The historical aspect formed the main theme of her essay. 她的论文的主题是由历史观点贯穿起来的。 3. We will deal with events in historical sequence. 我们将按照历史上的先后顺序研究这些事件。 4. Let\'s look at this from a historical standpoint. 让我们从历史的观点来看待这一切。', '副词: historically 名词: historicalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('finance', '[\'faɪnæns]', 'n.金融；财政；资金 vt.给 ... 提供资金；负担经费', '1. He is a well-known expert in finance. 他是知名的金融专家。 2. The Chancellor of the Exchequer is the minister in charge of finance in Britain. 英国财政大臣是负责财政的大臣。 3. Unless we can get more finance, we\'ll have to close the store. 除非我们能得到更多的资金，我们将不得不关闭这家商店。 4. The repairs to the school will be financed by the educational department. 学校的修缮将由教育部门出资。', '形容词: financeable 过去式: financed 过去分词: financed 现在分词: financing 第三人称单数: finances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('control', '[kən\'troʊl]', 'n.掌控；控制；管制；克制；操作装置 v.控制；支配；掌管；抑制；克制', '1. Don\'t worry, we have everything under control. 别担心,一切都在我们掌控之中。 2. Inflation has got out of control. 通货膨胀失去了控制。 3. The government has imposed strict controls over the import of luxury goods. 政府对奢侈品的进口采取了严格的管制。 4. He has little control over his emotions. 他控制不住自己的感情。 5. The firemen were unable to control the blaze. 消防队员无法控制这场大火。', '形容词: controllable 名词: controllability 过去式: controlled 过去分词: controlled 现在分词: controlling 第三人称单数: controls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rubbish', '[\'rʌbɪʃ]', 'n.垃圾；废物；废话；碎屑 v.贬损', '1. The dustman comes once a week to collect the rubbish. 垃圾工每周来收一次垃圾。 2. That new TV show is absolutely rubbish. 那个新的电视节目一点儿价值都没有。 3. He was gulled into buying rubbish. 他被骗买了废物。 4. I thought he talked a lot of rubbish. 我觉得他谈的都是些废话。 5. The film was rubbished by the critics. 影评家把这部影片贬得一无是处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('propaganda', '[ˌprɑːpə\'ɡændə]', 'n.宣传；宣传的内容', '1. Art may be used as a vehicle for propaganda. 艺术可用作宣传工具。 2. There has been a lot of anti-war propaganda. 一直有许多反战宣传。 3. She even helped us do propaganda among the women. 她甚至还帮助我们在妇女中间做宣传工作。 4. here has been so much propaganda against smoking that many people have given it up. 反对吸烟的宣传很多,许多人因而戒了烟。', '形容词: propagandistic 副词: propagandistically 名词: propagandism');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('modest', '[\'mɑːdɪst]', 'adj.谦虚的；适度的；端庄的；有节制的', '1. We should be modest and prudent. 我们应该谦虚谨慎。 2. She is very modest about her success. 她对自己的成就很谦虚。 3. I bought the house at a modest price. 我以适中的价格买下了这所房子。 4. Young girls must be modest in speech, dress and behavior. 年轻姑娘必须言词谨慎，衣着得体，行为端庄。', '副词: modestly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nest', '[nest]', 'n.巢；窝 vt.为 ... 筑巢；嵌入 vi.筑巢；寻找鸟巢', '1. The blackbird\'s nest contained four eggs. 黑鹂巢里有四个蛋。 2. The male hunts for food while his mate guards the nest. 雌性动物守巢时，雄性动物猎食。 3. The bird is building a nest of straw and twigs. 这只鸟在用稻草和小树枝筑巢。 4. The swallow has made a nest under our eaves. 燕子在我们的屋檐下垒了一个窝。 5. The boy was nesting for the little birds. 这个男孩正在为这些小鸟筑巢。 6. The swallows nested under the eaves. 燕子在屋檐下筑巢。', '过去式: nested 过去分词: nested 现在分词: nesting 第三人称单数: nests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('digest', '[\'dɑɪdʒɛst]', 'n.摘要 vt.消化；理解 vi.消化', '1. This is a digest of the week\'s news. 这是一周新闻摘要。 2. The baby is too small to digest meat. 婴儿太小,吃肉不消化。 3. Saliva helps one chew and digest food. 唾液能帮助咀嚼和消化食物。 4. It took me some time to digest what I had heard. 我花了一些时间才把听到的东西弄明白。 5. This rich food doesn\'t digest easily. 这种油腻的食物不易消化。', '过去式: digested 过去分词: digested 现在分词: digesting 第三人称单数: digests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('goal', '[ɡoʊl]', 'n.球门；目标；得分', '1. No. 6 gave a long shot, but missed the goal. 6号来了一个长射，但没有射中球门。 2. He has achieved his goal. 他已经实现了他的目标。 3. If we lose sight of the goal, we cease to be Communists. 如果忘记了这个目标，我们就不再是共产党员了。 4. That last goal was a beauty. 最後进去的那个球真漂亮。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bound', '[baʊnd]', 'adj.必定的；有义务的；受约束的；装订的 vi.跳；跳跃前进；猛涨 n.跳跃；范围；界限 动词bind的过去式和过去分词形式', '1. It\'s bound to rain soon. 过一会儿肯定会下雨。 2. You are not legally bound to answer these questions. 在法律上，你没有义务非回答这些问题不可。 3. We are bound hand and foot by the contract, so we are unable to help you. 我们受到合同的约束而不能帮你。 4. He bought a bound volume of the magazine. 他买了一本该杂志的合订本。 5. The dog bounded down the hill. 狗跳跃着朝山下跑去。 6. With one bound, he was over the wall. 他纵身一跃就跳过了墙。', '过去式: bounded 过去分词: bounded 现在分词: bounding 第三人称单数: bounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eject', '[i\'dʒekt]', 'v.喷射；放逐；驱逐', '1. When endangered,octopuses eject an inky substance,which is used as a screen. 遇到危险的时候，章鱼能够喷射一种墨水状的液体，掩蔽它们逃走。 2. When triggered,these cells eject poison-tipped barbs that help the jellyfish catch food in the ocean. 当受到触发时，这些细胞喷射出有助于海蜇在海洋中捕捉食物的有毒倒钩。 3. If the voters go further and eject Mr Harper, that, sadly, will not be because they have been convinced by the cerebral Mr Dion\'s worthy carbon tax. 如果选民进一步驱逐哈珀，遗憾的是，这不会发生，因为他们在脑海里确信狄恩应得烟尘排放税。 4. He says Pyongyang\'s recent moves to eject international inspectors and resume activity at its main nuclear reactor have dealt a serious blow to the process. 他说，平壤最近驱逐国际核查人员以及恢复其主要核反应堆的作法都对和谈进程造成了严重的打击。', '形容词: ejectable 过去式: ejected 过去分词: ejected 现在分词: ejecting 第三人称单数: ejects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('settle', '[\'setl]', 'v.解决；定居；安顿；平静；结算 n.背长椅，座位；定居，安顿', '1. If you pay for both of us now, we can settle up later. 你要是现在先付清咱们两人的帐，事后咱们俩再细算。 2. An official mission was sent to settle the dispute. 一个官方使团被派去解决争端。 3. The two companies settled out of court. 两家公司在法院外了结了争端。 4. They moved the local people and settle them in another place. 他们把当地人迁移到别处定居。', '形容词: settleable 过去式: settled 过去分词: settled 现在分词: settling 第三人称单数: settles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poet', '[\'poʊət]', 'n.诗人', '1. A great poet is a master melody. 大诗人也是音律大师。 2. It is written by an obscure young poet. 这是一位不知名的年轻诗人写的。 3. The poet expressed his burning passion for the woman he loved. 诗人表达了他对所爱的女子火一般的激情。 4. He was awarded the poet laureate by the queen. 他被女王封为桂冠诗人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('convince', '[kən\'vɪns]', 'vt.使确信；使信服；说服', '1. I try to convince him of the reality of the danger. 我试图使他相信危险的确存在。 2. It took many hours to convince me of his guilt. 研究了许多个小时我才相信他有罪。 3. He convinced me of his sincerity. 他使我确信他的真诚。 4. There was not an atom of evidence to convince him. 没有一点能使他信服的证据。', '形容词: convincible 名词: convincement 过去式: convinced 过去分词: convinced 现在分词: convincing 第三人称单数: convinces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('legacy', '[\'leɡəsi]', 'n.遗赠物；先人或过去遗留下来的东西 adj.[计算机]旧系统的', '1. He left me a small legacy in a nuncupative will, as a token of his kindness to me. 他囗头遗言上遗留给我一点小小遗产作为他对我关爱的表征。 2. These are the cultural legacies of the Renaissance. 这些是文艺复兴时期的文化遗产。', '名词复数: legacies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appeal', '[ə\'piːl]', 'n.恳求；呼吁；上诉；吸引力 n.(体育比赛中)诉请裁决 v.呼吁；有吸引力；求助；诉请', '1. Their appeal for help went unheeded. 他们求助的呼吁未受到注意。 2. He made one last appeal to his father to forgive him. 他最後一次恳求父亲宽恕他。 3. His appeal to a higher court was set aside. 他的上诉被驳回。 4. The judge rejected the appeal made by the prisoner for a new trial. 法官驳回了犯人提出重新审理的上诉。 5. The police appealed to the crowd not to panic. 警方向群众呼吁不要惊慌。', '形容词: appealable 名词: appealability 过去式: appealed 过去分词: appealed 现在分词: appealing 第三人称单数: appeals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dear', '[dɪr]', 'adj.亲爱的；宝贵的；昂贵的 n.可爱的人；亲爱的人 adv.高价地 int.啊；哎呀(用以表示惊奇、害怕以及其他强烈感情)', '1. They interred their dear comrade in the arms. 他们埋葬了他们亲爱的战友。 2. Dear Julia, I hope you\'re feeling better now. 亲爱的朱莉,我希望你现在感觉能好点。 3. Dear young ladies--I am deeply touched by your remembrance. 亲爱的姑娘们，你们的纪念品使我深受感动。 4. He lost everything that was dear to him. 他所珍贵的一切都损失了。 5. Thank you, you are a dear! 谢谢你,你真是个好人！ 6. If you want to make money, buy cheap and sell dear. 要想赚钱就得贱买贵卖。 7. M: Oh dear! Now he can\'t find his wallet! 我的天啊!现在他又找不到他的钱包了。', '副词: dearly 比较级: dearer 最高级: dearest 名词: dearness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('note', '[noʊt]', 'n.笔记；便条；纸币；音符；票据；注解；音调 vt.注意；记录；注解', '1. Students should take notes during the lectures. 学生们上课应该做笔记。 2. Seeing nobody at home, he decided to leave a note. 看到没人在家,他决定留下一个便条。 3. I\'d like to break this 50 dollars note. 我想把这张50美元的纸币换开。 4. It was only momentary--a sad note as out of an old song--and then it was gone. 这只是个瞬间的回忆--如同一首老歌中一个悲伤的音符--随后就消失了。 5. I failed to note that he had left. 我没有注意到他已经走了。', '名词: noter 过去式: noted 过去分词: noted 现在分词: noting 第三人称单数: notes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('employee', '[ɪm\'plɔɪiː]', 'n.雇员', '1. This employee was dismissed for laziness. 这名雇员因为懒惰而被解雇。 2. Their situations are now reversed as employee has become employer. 他们双方的地位转换了，雇员成了雇主。 3. The boss struck off 100 dollars from the salary of the employee as fine. 老板从这个雇员的工资里扣除100美元作为罚款。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('precedent', '[\'presɪdənt]', 'n.先例；惯例 adj.先前的；在先的', '1. This decision creates a dangerous precedent. 这个决定开创了一个危险的先例。 2. My decision does not constitute a precedent. 我的决定下不为例。 3. This intervention in another nation\'s affairs has set a precedent which we hope other countries will not follow. 对别国事物的这种干涉开了一个先例，我们希望其他国家不要模仿。 4. The President followed historical precedent in forming the Cabinet. 总统遵循历史惯例来组成内阁。 5. The precedent decision should be understood before we act. 在采取行动之前我们应该弄明白先前的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('garden', '[\'ɡɑːrdn]', 'n.园地(用于种植花、果、菜) v.从事园艺活动', '1. Mary talked with me across the garden fence. 玛丽和我隔着花园篱笆交谈。 2. He dunged his vegetable garden regularly. 他经常给他的菜园施肥。 3. He\'s been gardening all day. 他在园中干了一整天。', '过去式: gardened 过去分词: gardened 现在分词: gardening 第三人称单数: gardens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('destructive', '[dɪ\'strʌktɪv]', 'adj.破坏性的；有害的', '1. The destructive force of the storm is huge. 暴风雨的破坏力是巨大的。 2. Are all small children so destructive? 是不是儿童都喜欢破坏? 3. Jealousy is an extremely destructive emotion. 嫉妒是一种极其破坏性的情绪。 4. A locust is a kind of destructive insect. 蝗虫是一种害虫。', '副词: destructively 名词: destructiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('horizon', '[hə\'raɪzn]', 'n.地平线；眼界；范围', '1. The lights were blinking on the horizon. 灯光在地平线上闪烁着。 2. The sun rose above the horizon. 太阳升到地平线上。 3. Forget the horizon then you can fly high. 要想飞得高,就要把地平线忘掉。 4. Travel broadens one\'s horizons. 旅行可开阔人的眼界。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('numb', '[nʌm]', 'adj.麻木的；失去知觉的 vt.使麻木；使失去知觉', '1. My fingers were so numb that I could hardly write. 我的手指都麻木了几乎不能写字。 2. I\'ve just been to the dentist and my face is still numb. 我刚刚去看了牙医，脸上现在还没知觉呢。 3. The anaesthetic made his whole face go numb. 麻醉药使他的整张脸失去了知觉。 4. His leg was numbed by the intense pain. 他的腿因剧痛而麻木。', '副词: numbly 比较级: number 最高级: numbest 名词: numbness 过去式: numbed 过去分词: numbed 现在分词: numbing 第三人称单数: numbs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('well-known', '[\'wel\'noʊn]', 'adj.出名的；众所周知的', '1. He is little known as an artist. 他是个不出名的艺术家。 2. Our silks are known for good quality. 我们的丝绸是以质量出名的。 3. His championship of women\'s rights is well known. 他提倡女权是众所周知的。 4. Auroras are known to have many shapes and colors. 众所周知的是极光有许多形状和颜色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('summit', '[\'sʌmɪt]', 'n.顶点；最高阶层', '1. It was a warm climb to the summit. 向顶峰攀登时身上都热起来了。 2. The Hungarian view is magnificent from the summit of the mountains. 从群山之颠看到的匈牙利景色非常壮丽。 3. The news is all about the latest summit meeting. 这条消息是关於最近的首脑级会议的。 4. He attained the summit of his ambition. 他达到了追求的最高目标。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('title', '[\'taɪtl]', 'n.标题；称号；头衔；权利 v.加标题于；授予…称号', '1. What\'s the title of her new book? 她的新书书名是什么？ 2. The title just won\'t come to mind. 那个标题就是想不起来。 3. If you lose, you\'re given a really humiliating title. 如果你输了,你会被标上一个很丢脸的称号。 4. The emperor conferred a title on the brave soldier. 皇上授予这勇敢的士兵一头衔。', '过去式: titled 过去分词: titled 现在分词: titling 第三人称单数: titles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('world', '[wɜːrld]', 'n.世界；地球；世人；世间；领域 adj.世界的', '1. He is the richest man in the world. 他是世界上最富有的人。 2. There is a map of the world on the wall. 墙上有张世界地图。 3. Long ago, people believed that the world was flat. 很久以前人们相信地球是平的。 4. The world\'s natural ecosystems act as a buffer. 地球上的自然生态系统起着一种缓冲的作用。 5. I suppose all the compositions are world famous pieces. 我想所有的曲子都是世界名曲吧。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sculpture', '[\'skʌlptʃər]', 'n.雕塑；雕刻 v.雕刻；雕塑；刻蚀；当雕刻师', '1. He was a professor of sculpture at the Academy. 他在学院是一位雕塑教授。 2. The smooth contour of the sculpture is wonderful. 雕塑物平滑的轮廓线简直太美了。 3. She studied sculpture at art school. 她在美术学校学习雕刻。 4. There are two horses sculptured in bronze at the gate. 在大门口有两匹用青铜雕塑的马。', '形容词: sculptural 副词: sculpturally 过去式: sculptured 过去分词: sculptured 现在分词: sculpturing 第三人称单数: sculptures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('instrumental', '[ˌɪnstrə\'mentl]', 'adj.仪器的；乐器的；有帮助的；可做为手段的 n.器乐曲；[语]工具格', '1. These tests require an extremely sophisticated instrumental effort. 这些试验需要极其尖端仪器才能办到。 2. I like instrumental music better than vocal music. 我喜欢器乐胜于声乐。 3. His instrumental works are popular amongst the students. 他的器乐曲在学生中很受欢迎。 4. Your advice has been instrumental in settling the question. 你的劝告对决这个问题是有帮助的。 5. His instrumental works are popular amongst the students. 他的器乐曲在学生中很受欢迎。', '副词: instrumentally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('well', '[wel]', 'adv.很好地；相当地 int.好吧；啊 adj.健康的；良好的；适宜的 n.井；源泉；楼梯井 v.涌出', '1. She speaks English very well. 她英语讲得很好。 2. I can\'t sleep well because the tap is dripping. 龙头漏水,吵得我睡不好觉。 3. It was well worth waiting for. 这件事倒是很值得等待。 4. Let me think for a minute. Well, I guess so. 让我想想,好吧,我想可以。 5. Is she well enough to travel? 她身体康复, 能够旅行了吗? 6. The police found the lost treasure in an abandoned well. 警察在一口废弃的井里找到了丢失的财宝。', '比较级: better 最高级: best 过去式: welled 过去分词: welled 现在分词: welling 第三人称单数: wells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stage', '[steɪdʒ]', 'n.舞台；戏剧；阶段；步骤；行程 v.上演；举行；组织；筹划；使出现', '1. She stood alone on the enormous stage. 她孤零零地站在巨大的舞台上。 2. He quitted the stage of politics. 他退出了政治舞台。 3. Novels are often adapted for the stage. 小说常常改编为戏剧。 4. The disease is still in its primary stage. 这疾病仍然在初发阶段。 5. She asserted that she was going to stage a musical comedy. 她说她要组织演出一部音乐喜剧。', '名词: stageful 过去式: staged 过去分词: staged 现在分词: staging 第三人称单数: stages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whoever', '[huː\'evər]', 'pron.无论是谁；不管谁；任何人', '1. Whoever leaves the office should tell me. 无论是谁离开办公室都应该告诉我。 2. Whoever visits the town will be welcome. 不管谁来镇上参观都受欢迎。 3. Whoever commits the crime shall be sentenced to ten years in prison. 任何人犯了此罪就要被判处十年徒刑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loosen', '[\'luːsn]', 'vt.松开；放松；放宽 vi.变松；松弛', '1. I loosened my tie, but I didn\'t take it off. 我松开了领带，但是没有把它解下来。 2. Can you loosen the lid of this jar? 你能把这个瓶盖松开吗? 3. A emperor should never loosen the grasp of power. 君主应永不放松对权力的掌控。 4. The government has loosened restrictions on the sale of liquor. 政府已经放宽了对销售烈酒的限制。 5. The government\'s control over the newspapers has loosened in recent years. 近年来政府对报纸的控制已经变松了。', '过去式: loosened 过去分词: loosened 现在分词: loosening 第三人称单数: loosens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resemble', '[rɪ\'zembl]', 'v.与…相似；像', '1. The brothers resemble each other in taste. 那对兄弟兴趣相似。 2. She resembles her sister in appearance but not in character. 她和她姐姐外貌相似，但性格不同。 3. You resemble your mother very closely. 你非常像你的母亲。', '名词: resembler 过去式: resembled 过去分词: resembled 现在分词: resembling 第三人称单数: resembles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('merchant', '[\'mɜːrtʃənt]', 'n.商人；店主；专家 adj.商业的；商船的 n.（班轮提单）货方；签约方', '1. The merchant had received a shipment of tea. 这个商人收到了一船茶叶。 2. The merchant decided to use camels to carry his goods across the desert. 商人决定用骆驼载运货物穿过沙漠。 3. The merchant\'s cash sales each day were $300. 那店主一天有300美元的现金售货收入。 4. Art experts, who have already dated the painting to this time, say the Heidelberg discovery is a breakthrough and the earliest mention linking the merchant\'s wife to the portrait. 美术专家们还称，关于此画，海德尔堡的发现是一个突破，并且是最早提出把商人的妻子和人物肖像结合起来这一说法的。 5. This is a merchant bank. 这是个商业银行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('infant', '[\'ɪnfənt]', 'n.婴儿；幼儿 adj.婴儿的；初期的；幼稚的', '1. She gazed at the newborn infant and smiled. 她望着这个初生的婴儿笑了。 2. My sister\'s infant is very lovely. 我姐姐的小婴儿非常可爱。 3. A 35-day-old male infant was scheduled for bilateral inguinal herniorrhaphy. 摘要一个三十五天大的幼儿接受二沟腹股沟疝气门诊手术。 4. Infant family education is an important education environment which can\'t be irreplaceable by preschool education and social education. 幼儿家庭教育是幼儿园教育和社会教育所不能替代的重要教育环境。 5. Infant mortality is still very high in some developing countries. 某些发展中国家的婴儿死亡率仍然很高。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impatient', '[ɪm\'peɪʃnt]', 'adj.不耐烦的；急躁的', '1. He tends to snap at people when he gets impatient. 他一不耐烦的时候就对人没有好声气。 2. The impatient teacher slapped the student. 这位不耐烦的老师掌击了学生。 3. Your impatient self clearly suffers from a similar fixed cost of carrying out subtraction. 你身上那个急躁的自我，显然在实施减法时承受着类似的固定成本。', '副词: impatiently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('panda', '[\'pændə]', 'n.熊猫', '1. I have never seen a panda. 我从未见过熊猫。 2. The panda is now a rare animal. 熊猫现在是稀有动物。 3. Pandas are loved by people all over the world. 熊猫被全世界的人们喜爱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discover', '[dɪ\'skʌvər]', 'v.发现；偶然撞见；发觉', '1. He was later discovered to have been a spy. 后来发现他原来是间谍。 2. The fact is that he did not discover it. 事实是他没有发现它。 3. I discovered him kissing my wife. 我撞见他在吻我的妻子。 4. We discovered that our luggage had been stolen. 我们发觉行李被偷了.', '形容词: discoverable 名词: discovery 过去式: discovered 过去分词: discovered 现在分词: discovering 第三人称单数: discovers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('marginal', '[\'mɑːrdʒɪnl]', 'adj.边际的；末端的；仅以微弱多数获胜的；微小的', '1. Economists call these marginal changes. 经济学家称这些为边际的变化。 2. The marginal illustration is very interesting. 页边的插图很有趣。 3. He won the most marginal seat by only two votes. 他只以两票的微弱优势当选。 4. He had a very marginal victory with only 180 more votes in his favor. 他仅以180票的微弱优势赢得了胜利。', '副词: marginally 名词: marginality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hi', '[haɪ]', 'int.嗨(引人注意时的喊声；打招呼)', '1. Hi there, buddy! 嘿，老兄！ 2. Hi there, Stevens. 你好，史蒂文斯。 3. Hi! Great show, eh? 你好！好节目，是吗？ 4. Hi, there. 嗨，你好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pause', '[pɔːz]', 'n.暂停；中止；犹豫不决 vi.停顿；中止', '1. There will be a brief pause in the program. 这个计划可能需要暂停一下。 2. I made the classic mistake of clapping in a pause in the music! 我在乐曲演奏暂停的间歇鼓起掌来，真是大错特错！ 3. There was a pregnant pause before she answered my question. 她耐人寻味地停顿了一下才回答我的问题。 4. His words were followed by a pregnant pause. 他说完话，接着是一段意味深长的停顿。 5. He paused before making the important decision. 他在作出这个重要决定前犹豫不决。', '过去式: paused 过去分词: paused 现在分词: pausing 第三人称单数: pauses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rose', '[roʊz]', 'n.玫瑰；蔷薇 adj.玫瑰色的；玫瑰的 动词rise的过去式.', '1. He plucked a rose for his lover. 他为情人摘了一朵玫瑰花。 2. I found him pruning his roses. 我看到他正在给玫瑰修剪枝条。 3. Botanists refer this flower to the rose family. 植物学家将这花归入蔷薇科。 4. The box of chocolate is wrapped in rose paper. 这盒巧克力外面有一层玫瑰色的包装纸。 5. The mist quickly dissipated as the sun rose. 太阳升起时雾很快就消散了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('worldwide', '[\'wɜːrldwaɪd]', 'adj.全世界的 adv.在全世界', '1. The story has attracted worldwide attention. 这件事已经引起了全世界的关注。 2. Gasoline now has an almost worldwide use. 汽油在全世界范围内被广泛使用。 3. Our hotel have a worldwide reputation for good service. 我们出色的饭店服务享誉世界。 4. Our society expanded into a worldwide organization. 我们的协会扩大成一个世界性组织。 5. More than 100 million votes were cast worldwide. 全世界投票总数超过1亿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invitation', '[ˌɪnvɪ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.邀请；邀请函；招待；招致，引诱', '1. I appreciate your invitation. 感谢你的邀请。 2. He made a refusal to her invitation. 他拒绝了她的邀请。 3. Nobody in the office had received an invitation to the party. 在办公室里没有人收到邀请函去参加这个宴会。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('throw', '[θroʊ]', 'v.扔；投；掷；抛 n.抛；投掷', '1. Pick out some good apples from the box, and throw away the rest. 把好苹果从盒子里捡出来,剩下的扔了。 2. The trees threw long shadows across the lawn. 树在草坪上都投下长长的影子。 3. It\'s your turn to throw the dice. 轮到你掷骰子了。 4. He threw the stone in the air. 他把石头抛向空中。 5. My nephew lives only a stone\'s throw from my house. 我侄子住得离我家很近。', '名词: thrower 过去式: threw 过去分词: thrown 现在分词: throwing 第三人称单数: throws');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('avenue', '[\'ævənuː]', 'n.林荫道；大街；途径手段', '1. He stands on the corner of a wide avenue. 他站在宽阔的林荫道的角落里。 2. I meet him by chance on Fifth Avenue. 我偶然在第大街上遇到他。 3. The avenue was crowded with people. 大街上挤满了人。 4. Hard work is a sure avenue to success. 勤奋是可靠的成功之道。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('denounce', '[dɪ\'naʊns]', 'v.谴责；告发；通告废除', '1. The minister\'s action was denounced in the newspaper. 部长的行为受到报界的指责。 2. American trade policies have been denounced by some European governments. 一些欧洲政府指责美国的贸易政策。 3. They denounced him to the police as a criminal. 他们向警方告发他是罪犯。 4. Somebody denounced him to the military police as a spy. 有人向宪兵队告发他为间谍。', '名词: denouncement 过去式: denounced 过去分词: denounced 现在分词: denouncing 第三人称单数: denounces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('radical', '[\'rædɪkl]', 'adj.激进的；彻底的；基本的 n.激进分子', '1. I know you are radical in your thinking, but don\'t go too far. 我知道你思想激进,但不要走的太远。 2. He took up a radical position on this issue. 他对这个问题抱着激进的态度。 3. They called for a radical reform of our tax system. 他们要求对税收制度进行根本改革。 4. Lambert did not reach the more radical conclusion. 兰伯特还没有达到更本质的结论。 5. Ted is a fire-eating radical. 泰德是个咄咄逼人的激进份子。', '副词: radically 名词: radicalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yours', '[jərz]', 'pron.你的；你们的', '1. My feelings are in unison with yours. 我的感情与你的感情是一致的。 2. His problem is similar to yours. 他的问题和你的相似。 3. We must fit our plan in with yours. 我们必须使我们的计划与你们的协调一致。 4. His bicycle is of better quality than yours. 他的自行车质量比你们的好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('much', '[mʌtʃ]', 'adj.许多的 adv.很；非常；几乎 n.许多', '1. The President\'s speech provoked much discussion. 总统的演说引发了许多议论。 2. All the furniture in the room had much carving. 房间里所有的家具上都有许多雕刻。 3. My plans are still very much in embryo. 我的计划在很大程度上仍在酝酿中。 4. I would very much like to see you again. 我很想再见到你。 5. Much has been written. 大量内容已被写过了', '比较级: more 最高级: most');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('supervise', '[\'suːpərvaɪz]', 'vt.监督；管理；指导', '1. I supervised the workers loading the lorry. 我监督工人把货物装上卡车。 2. The chief clerk supervises the work of the department. 文书组长负责监督该部门的工作。 3. She wants to supervise the cosmetics shop. 她想自己管理那间化妆品店。 4. How many people did you supervise on your last job? 你的上一份工作需要管理多少人?', '过去式: supervised 过去分词: supervised 现在分词: supervising 第三人称单数: supervises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('silicon', '[\'sɪlɪkən]', 'n.硅', '1. Now people can produce a wafer silicon. 现在人们能够生产一种硅晶薄片。 2. Silicon is usually added by co-evaporation. 硅通常是通过共蒸发来加入的。 3. In computers, these diodes are primarily germanium or silicon crystals. 在计算机中,这些二极管基本上是锗或硅晶体二极管。', '简写符号: Si');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accustomed', '[ə\'kʌstəmd]', 'adj.习惯了的；通常的', '1. He was accustomed to command, not to entreat. 他习惯于发号施令，而不是恳求他人。 2. You will soon get accustomed to the climate here. 你会很快习惯这里的气候的。 3. I might have been incredulous had I not been accustomed to such responses. 若非我已经习惯了这样的回答，我可能不敢轻易相信。 4. He is accustom to get up at six. 他习惯于6点起床。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ambulance', '[\'æmbjələns]', 'n.救护车', '1. An ambulance dashed to the scene of the accident. 救护车风驰电掣赶往事故现场。 2. An ambulance was racing along with its sirens wailing. 救护车响着警报急驰而过。 3. The injured man was fairly far gone by the time the ambulance arrived. 救护车到时那伤者已生命垂危。 4. The light was red but the ambulance drove straight through. 红灯亮着,但救护车闯了过去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('road', '[roʊd]', 'n.路；道路；途径；方法', '1. A fall of rocks blocked the road. 掉落的岩石把路封住了。 2. The road was blocked by a huge rock. 道路被一块大石头堵住了。 3. The rough road made the car vibrate. 崎岖不平的道路使车颠簸得很厉害。 4. This is the high road to democracy. 这是通向民主的直接途径。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disable', '[dɪs\'eɪbl]', 'v.使 ... 失去能力', '1. He was disabled from walking by the accident. 由于车祸，他不能走路了。 2. Old age disabled him for hard labour. 年迈使他不能干繁重的工作。 3. The soldier disabled by wounds in his leg is buried in sadness. 那个腿部受伤致残的士兵正沉浸在悲哀之中。', '形容词: disabling 副词: disablingly 名词: disablement 过去式: disabled 过去分词: disabled 现在分词: disabling 第三人称单数: disables');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stocking', '[\'stɑːkɪŋ]', 'n.长袜，（女用）长筒袜 动词stock的现在分词形式.', '1. I ripped my stocking on a nail. 一个钉子挂破了我的袜子。 2. The thief masked his face with a stocking. 那贼套上长筒袜遮住脸。 3. The boy is one meter tall in his stocking feet. 这个小男孩不穿鞋的身高是一米。', '形容词: stockinged');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tense', '[tens]', 'adj.紧张的；绷紧的；拉紧的 v.拉紧；使紧绷 n.(动词)时态', '1. Try to act naturally, even if you\'re tense. 即使紧张也不要做作。 2. It is difficult to be natural when one is tense. 人在紧张的时候很难泰然自若。 3. She was gently massaging the tense muscles of his neck. 她温柔地按摩着他脖子上绷紧的肌肉。 4. She tensed, hearing that noise again. 她再次听到那个声音就紧张起来。 5. The verb is in the present tense. 这个动词使用的是现在时态。', '副词: tensely 比较级: tenser 最高级: tensest 名词: tenseness 过去式: tensed 过去分词: tensed 现在分词: tensing 第三人称单数: tenses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('silly', '[\'sɪli]', 'adj.愚蠢的；琐屑的；可笑的；犯晕的 n.（通常指小孩子）淘气鬼；傻孩子', '1. The silly ending robs the plot of any credibility. 这愚蠢的结尾使得整个情节变得一点都不可信。 2. Don\'t get upset over silly things that people say. 不要在意人们的闲言碎语。 3. I look pretty silly in this dress. 我穿这条裙看上去很可笑。 4. I took a swing at him and knocked him silly. 我挥拳打了他一下, 把他打得晕头转向。 5. Listen, silly, we have to leave now. 听着,小淘气鬼,我们现在得走了。', '副词: sillily 比较级: sillier 最高级: silliest 名词: silliness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('satire', '[\'sætaɪər]', 'n.讽刺文；讽刺', '1. Satire is a high and subtle art. 讽刺是一门崇高而又含蓄的艺术。 2. Politicians are legitimate targets for satire. 政治家理所当然是讽刺的靶子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dwelling', '[\'dwelɪŋ]', 'n.住处；住宅', '1. He changed his dwelling recently. 他最近搬了家。 2. The smoke betrays where the dwelling lies. 炊烟起处有人家。 3. Our stable abuts against his dwelling. 我们的马厩和他的住所毗连。 4. We weathered out the winter in a lonely dwelling. 我们在一所偏僻的房子里熬过了冬天。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('choice', '[tʃɔɪs]', 'n.选择；挑选；抉择 adj.上等的；精选的', '1. I believe that he can make a judicious choice. 我相信他能作出明智的选择。 2. The choice rests entirely with you. 这完全由你来选择。 3. We have no choice except to trust ourselves. 我们必须依靠自己,没有其他选择。 4. He is cautious in his choice of words. 他措辞很谨慎。 5. We select only the choicest apples for our pies. 我们精选最好的苹果制作馅饼。', '副词: choicely 比较级: choicer 最高级: choicest 名词: choiceness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enlighten', '[ɪn\'laɪtn]', 'v.启发；开导；教导', '1. This book will enlighten the reader. 这本书将会启发读者。 2. Enlighten me with your thoughts on this matter. 你们在如下事件上的思想启发了我。 3. Can you enlighten me--I don\'t understand this proposal. 我不明白这条建议，你能不能启发我一下。 4. Can you enlighten me on this subject? 关于这个问题，你能指点我一下吗？', '名词: enlightener 过去式: enlightened 过去分词: enlightened 现在分词: enlightening 第三人称单数: enlightens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nationality', '[ˌnæʃə\'næləti]', 'n.国籍；民族', '1. She has dual nationality. 她有双重国籍。 2. She storied about her nationality. 她谎报自己的国籍。 3. There are two main nationalities in our village. 我们村子有两大民族。 4. The nation will combat all invaders. 这个民族将同所有的入侵者战斗。', '名词复数: nationalities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sweater', '[\'swetər]', 'n.毛衣；出汗者', '1. This woolen sweater may keep you warm in winter. 这件羊毛衫在冬天可以保暖。 2. She slipped into the sweater and dashed out of the door. 她匆匆穿上毛衣, 冲出门去。 3. He put on a thick sweater since it was cold in the morning. 早晨很冷，他穿上了一件厚毛衣。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bury', '[\'beri]', 'vt.埋葬；隐匿；专心致志；抛弃', '1. Even if you kill me, even if you bury me, I should rise again. 即使你杀了我 2. The funeral is tomorrow and they will bury the body after the church service. 葬礼明天举行，他们会在教堂仪式后埋葬遗体。 3. He likes to bury himself in the country. 他喜欢隐居乡间。 4. She had learnt to bury her feelings. 她已经学会了感情不外露。', '名词: burier 过去式: buried 过去分词: buried 现在分词: burying 第三人称单数: buries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('source', '[sɔːrs]', 'n.来源；发源地；原始资料 v.从...获得', '1. My wages are the principal source of my income. 薪金是我收入的主要来源。 2. Hard work is the ultimate source of success. 努力工作是成功之本。 3. Where is the source of the Yellow River? 黄河的发源地在哪儿？ 4. The library has quantities of reference sources. 该图书馆藏有大量可供参考的原始资料。 5. We source all the meat sold in our stores from British farms. 我们商店里卖的肉均从英国农场购进。', '过去式: sourced 过去分词: sourced 现在分词: sourcing 第三人称单数: sources');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('administer', '[əd\'mɪnɪstər]', 'vt.管理；执行；给与；用(药) vi.执行管理人职责；给与帮助', '1. He administered a large pension fund. 他管理一大笔养老金。 2. It takes brains to administer a large corporation. 管理大公司要有头脑。 3. The courts administer the law. 法院执行法律。 4. The government says it will administer relief to famine victims. 政府表示将向饥民发放救济品。 5. A administers upon the estate of B. 甲负责管理乙的遗产。', '形容词: administrable 过去式: administered 过去分词: administered 现在分词: administering 第三人称单数: administers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flare', '[fler]', 'n.闪光；闪光信号；[天]耀斑；(衣裙等)张开 v.闪光；闪耀；爆发；张开', '1. The flare of the match lit up his face. 火柴的光照亮了他的脸。 2. He stood ready to fire a warning flare. 他站着准备发出警告信号。 3. One possibility is that the blast was like an ultra-powerful solar flare. 一种可能的原因是这种爆炸很像有超级能量的太阳耀斑。 4. These flows occurred after violently unstable magnetic reconnection events above the Sun produced the flare. 这些在太阳表面上空剧烈而又不稳定的磁重联事件会产生耀斑。 5. A gust of wind made the candles flare. 一阵风吹得烛光摇曳。', '过去式: flared 过去分词: flared 现在分词: flaring 第三人称单数: flares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cook', '[kʊk]', 'n.厨师；炊事员 v.烹调；烧煮；捏造；纂改(账目)', '1. The cook went to see the cake left in the oven. 炊事员去照看炉子里的蛋糕了。 2. They engaged a cook for the summer. 那个夏天他们雇了一个厨子。 3. He was a cook before his demobilization. 他复员以前是一名炊事员。 4. Will she cook dinner this evening? 她今晚要做晚饭吗？', '过去式: cooked 过去分词: cooked 现在分词: cooking 第三人称单数: cooks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fuss', '[fʌs]', 'n.大惊小怪；小题大作；强烈不满或争吵 vi.无事自扰；焦急；对小事激动 vt.扰乱；使焦躁', '1. Stop all this fuss and get on with your work. 别大惊小怪的闹了，继续干你的活儿去吧。 2. I do not want to make a fuss over such a trifle. 我不想为这种小事大惊小怪。 3. That\'s why we\'re making such a fuss over her. 所以我们才为她这么小题大作。 4. There is sure to be a fuss when my parents find the window is broken. 我父母发现窗子被打破后，一定会有一番斥责。 5. Stop fussing and eat your food! 别大惊小怪的，吃你的东西吧！ 6. Don\'t fuss me while I\'m driving. 我开车时别打搅我.', '名词: fusser 过去式: fussed 过去分词: fussed 现在分词: fussing 第三人称单数: fusses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('right', '[raɪt]', 'adj.正确的；对的；右边的；合适的；重要的；完全的 adv.正确地；直接地；向右；恰恰，就；立即；完全地 n.权利；道理；正确；右边；右派 v.扶直；纠正；公正对待；补偿；恢复平衡', '1. In general, I think we\'re on the right track. 总的看来,我想我们走的路子是正确的。 2. After some introspection, I think you are right. 经过了自省后,我认为你是对的。 3. The bus station is on the right side. 公共汽车站在右边。 4. She is the right girl for me; I need no one else. 她就是我要找的女孩,我不要其他人。 5. We had taken a wrong turning,but a policeman put us right. 我们转错了弯,但有一位警察给我们指出了正确的方向。 6. I have the right to ask for an explanation. 我有权要求一个解释。 7. I had to right the picture before I could feel comfortable. 我得把这幅画扶正才能感到舒服。', '比较级: righter 最高级: rightest 名词: righter 过去式: righted 过去分词: righted 现在分词: righting 第三人称单数: rights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bureaucracy', '[bjʊ\'rɑːkrəsi]', 'n.官僚制度；官僚主义；官僚', '1. All this is a product of corrupt bureaucracy. 这一切都是腐朽的官僚制度的产物。 2. The bureaucracy has become ossified. 官僚主义已变得僵化了。 3. The dead hand of bureaucracy is slowing our progress. 官僚主义的流毒拖慢了我们的进步。 4. You will find a lot of bureaucracy in this company. 你会在这个公司看到很严重的官僚作风。', '名词复数: bureaucracies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clash', '[klæʃ]', 'n.冲突；抵触；撞击声 vt.使…发出撞击声 vi.引起冲突', '1. A border clash between the two armies started the war. 双方军队在边境的冲突引发了战争。 2. In some ways,ours is a clash of cultures. 从某种意义上来说，我们的冲突是不同文化间的冲突。 3. The issue really boils down to a clash between left and right. 这场争论确实可归结为左派与右派之间的冲突。 4. His opinions clash against yours. 他的观点和你的相抵触。 5. She clashed these pans down on the floor. 她将这些盘子哗啦一声摔在地上。 6. The enemy armies clashed near the border. 敌军在边境附近发生冲突。', '过去式: clashed 过去分词: clashed 现在分词: clashing 第三人称单数: clashes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unexpected', '[ˌʌnɪk\'spektɪd]', 'adj.想不到的；意外的', '1. His reaction on this matter is unexpected. 没料到，他对这件事的反应是这样的。 2. Their unexpected arrival threw our plan into confusion. 他们的突然到来打乱了我们的计划。 3. Because of something unexpected, I wonder if I can change my appointment from Tuesday to Friday. 由于想不到的原因，我不知道是否可以把约会时间由星期二改到星期五。 4. What an unexpected pleasure! 这真是个意外的惊喜！', '副词: unexpectedly 名词: unexpectedness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('henceforth', '[ˌhens\'fɔːrθ]', 'adv.今后，此后', '1. The man said that he would work hard henceforth. 那人说从今以后他要努力工作了。 2. Henceforth it will be more difficult to avoid customs examination. 从此以后，避免海关检查将会更加困难。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('somewhere', '[\'sʌmwer]', 'adv.在某处；到某种程度；大约 n.某处', '1. Somewhere somebody sometimes does something good. 在某处某人有时做某些好事。 2. I must have seen you somewhere before. 我以前一定在某处见过你。 3. There is no one but wishes to get somewhere. 没有人不希望将来能有所成就。 4. He was a thinnish fellow, somewhere in his forties. 他瘦瘦的，大约四十多岁。 5. Somewhere somebody sometimes does something good. 在某处某人有时做某些好事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Latin', '[\'lætn]', 'n.拉丁语；拉丁人 adj.拉丁语的；拉丁人的；拉丁语系国家的', '1. Many languages have Latin as their base. 许多语言都以拉丁语为基础。 2. I can\'t get this Latin grammar into my head. 我理解不了这条拉丁语语法规则。 3. The reign of the Latin mind was now drawing to an end. 拉丁人思想的统治现在即将结束。 4. Very few students learn Latin now. 现在学拉丁语的学生少得很。', '动词: latinize 副词: latine');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dim', '[dɪm]', 'adj.暗淡的；模糊的；笨的 v.使暗淡；使失去光泽 n.车头近光灯；停车灯', '1. Most comets are so dim that they can not be seen by the naked eye. 彗星很暗淡,肉眼看不见。 2. He spoke with firmness, but his face was very sad and his eyes at times were dim. 他讲话时预期坚定，但面带愁容，时而眼神暗淡。 3. I made out two dim shapes in the gloom. 我在朦胧中看出有两个模糊的影子。 4. She is rather dim about the importance of keeping records. 她不明白作记录的重要性。 5. Old age hasn\'t dimmed her memory. 她虽然年事已高，但记忆并未模糊。', '副词: dimly 比较级: dimmer 最高级: dimmest 名词: dimness 过去式: dimmed 过去分词: dimmed 现在分词: dimming 第三人称单数: dims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('manipulate', '[mə\'nɪpjuleɪt]', 'vt.操纵；操作；控制；利用；(巧妙地)处理；篡改', '1. A clever politician know how to manipulate public opinion. 聪明的政客知道如何操纵公众舆论。 2. He is one of those who manipulate the market. 他是操纵市场者之一。 3. Do you know how to manipulate a computer ? 你知道怎样操作计算机吗? 4. She uses her charm to manipulate people. 她利用其魅力左右他人。', '形容词: manipulatable 副词: manipulatively 名词: manipulability 过去式: manipulated 过去分词: manipulated 现在分词: manipulating 第三人称单数: manipulates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('statistical', '[stə\'tɪstɪkl]', 'adj.统计的；统计学的', '1. It represents a statistical law. 它只是代表了一个统计的规律。 2. The analyst\'s judgement then must override mathematical and statistical significance. 分析家的判断必须超越数学和统计的有效性。 3. This is not intended to serve as a text of statistical techniques. 这并不是想把它变成统计学的技术课本。 4. The sample size in most deployments of Bollinger Bands is simply too small for statistical significance. 为统计学的意义在布林线的大多数推广的样品尺寸简单地是太小的。', '副词: statistically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strike', '[straɪk]', 'n.罢工；打击；殴打 v.打；撞；罢工；划燃', '1. The dockers are coming out on strike for higher wages. 码头工人将举行罢工要求增加工资。 2. The coalminers have been out on strike for several weeks now. 煤矿工人已罢工了几个星期。 3. The strike has delivered a heavy blow to the management. 这场罢工给资方以一个沉重打击。 4. His spirits sagged after that strike. 受到打击后他有点萎靡不振了。 5. He offered to strike the boy with his cane. 他威胁要用手杖打那个男孩。', '过去式: struck 过去分词: struck/stricken 现在分词: striking 第三人称单数: strikes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('memory', '[\'meməri]', 'n.记忆力；回忆；记忆；[计]存储', '1. He has a good visual memory. 他有良好的视觉记忆力。 2. She is always moaning about her bad memory. 她总是抱怨自己的记性不好。 3. His best music was inspired by the memory of his mother. 他最好的乐曲创作灵感来自怀念他的母亲。 4. These frightful experiences are branded on his memory. 这些可怕的经历深深印入他的记忆。', '名词复数: memories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('astronomy', '[ə\'strɑːnəmi]', 'n.天文学', '1. Physics and astronomy are cognate sciences. 物理学和天文学是相关联的科学。 2. Astronomy, as distinct from astrology, is an exact science. 天文学是一门严谨的科学，与占星术完全不同。 3. Astronomy is the scientific study of the sun, moon, and stars and other heaven bodies. 天文学是研究太阳、月亮、星星和其他天体的科学。 4. We\'re at cross-purposes: I\'m talking about astronomy, you\'re talking about astrology. 我们彼此误解了: 我谈的是天文学，你谈的是占星术。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blind', '[blaɪnd]', 'adj.盲目的；瞎的；未察觉的 vt.使失明；隐藏 adv.盲目地 n.百叶窗；幌子', '1. Love is blind and sometimes deaf. 爱情是盲目的,有时甚至是聋的。 2. She wants it so much that she became so stupid and blind. 她那么渴望,以致到了又笨又盲目的地步。 3. There\'s none so blind as those who won\'t see. 瞎子不算瞎,有眼不看才是瞎。 4. Without his spectacles, he is as blind as a bat. 没有眼镜,他是几乎全盲的。 5. The soldier was blinded in battle. 那个士兵在战斗中双目失明。 6. Most parents have a blind spot for their children. 大多数父母盲目地疼爱他们的孩子。 7. Something,such as a window shade or a Venetian blind,that hinders vision or shuts out light. 遮光物如窗帘或软百叶窗等能遮挡视线或挡住阳光的物体。', '副词: blindingly 比较级: blinder 最高级: blindest 名词: blindness 过去式: blinded 过去分词: blinded 现在分词: blinding 第三人称单数: blinds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alliance', '[ə\'laɪəns]', 'n.联盟；联姻；结盟 Alliance [地理名词].', '1. They broke up the alliance. 他们中止了联盟。 2. The alliance has been forged in the crucible of war. 这个联盟经受了战争的严峻考验。 3. Gerard required a different alliance to aid his career. 则杰拉就需要一个不同的联姻来帮助他的事业。 4. The two countries made an alliance. 两国结盟。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feminine', '[\'femənɪn]', 'adj.女性的；[语]阴性的', '1. Jewelry and lace are mostly feminine belongings. 珠宝和蕾丝大多是女性用品。 2. That\'s a feminine reaction. 这是女性特有的反应。 3. There are three genders in German: masculine, feminine and neuter. 德语中有三性: 阳性、 阴性和中性。', '副词: femininely 名词: feminineness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('onto', '[\'ɑːntə]', 'prep. 到 ... 上', '1. He grafted the branch onto the apple tree. 他将这根树枝嫁接到了苹果树上。 2. Historically, wafers were waxed onto a metal plate. 过去片子是用石蜡固定到金属板上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('penalty', '[\'penəlti]', 'n.处罚；惩罚；不利；罚球', '1. A penalty clause was written into the contract. 在合同中写入了一项罚款条款。 2. She has paid the penalty for her crimes with five years in prison. 她因犯罪受到惩罚被判刑五年。 3. One of the penalties of fame is that people point at you on the street. 当了名人的麻烦之一是在街上被人指指点点。 4. One of the penalties of fame is loss of privacy. 成名的弊端之一是失去了私人活动自由。', '名词复数: penalties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('card', '[kɑːrd]', 'n.纸牌；卡片；名片；<口>怪人；梳理机 v.把 ... 记入卡片；梳理', '1. They play cards every Friday. 他们每个星期五玩纸牌。 2. No one understood how I did the card trick. 谁也没有看出来我是怎样玩纸牌戏法的。 3. I have received eleven Christmas cards by now. 到现在为止，我已经收到了十一张圣诞卡片。 4. He listed all the members\' names on the card. 他把所有会员的名字都记在卡片上。', '名词: carder 过去式: carded 过去分词: carded 现在分词: carding 第三人称单数: cards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('postcard', '[\'poʊstkɑːrd]', 'n.明信片 adj.如画的', '1. He sent me a postcard from the United Nations. 他从联合国给我寄来一张明信片。 2. Excuse me, how much is a postcard to France? 打扰一下，寄往法国的明信片多少钱一张？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('defence', '[dɪ\'fens]', 'n.防御；答辩；防务', '1. Humour is a more effective defence than violence. 幽默是比暴力更有效的防御武器。 2. They planned the defence of the town. 他们订出了该城的防御计划。 3. They took up arms in defence of their country. 他们拿起武器保卫祖国。 4. The defence argues that the evidence is weak. 辩护律师提出理由认为证据不充分。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('training', '[\'treɪnɪŋ]', 'n.训练；培养 动词train的现在分词形式.', '1. The champion is in training for his next fight. 这位冠军为了下一场比赛正在进行训练。 2. They finished the preparatory training. 他们完成了预备训练。 3. The army training exercises ended with a mock battle. 军事训练演习以一场模拟战结束。 4. On the course she received a thorough training in every aspect of the job. 在训练班上，她接受了有关这个工作各方面的全面训练。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dividend', '[\'dɪvɪdend]', 'n.股息；红利；被除数；彩金；回报', '1. These shares pay a dividend of 1.5p. 这些股票的股息为1. 2. The company declared a large dividend at the end of the year. 公司在年底宣布分发高额股息。 3. The company was forced to pass its dividend. 该公司被迫到期不分红。 4. In 8 ÷ 2, 8 is the dividend. 在8除以2这个式子中,8是被除数。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('retail', '[\'riːteɪl]', 'n.零售 vt.零售；传述 adv.以零售形式', '1. They buy at wholesale and sell at retail. 他们大批地买进,再以零售方式卖出。 2. These biros retail at 70p. 这些圆珠笔零售价为70便士。 3. We should be able to retail most of these products to overseas customers. 我们应能够把这些产品的大部分卖给海外的顾客。 4. Who is responsible for retailing these rumors about him? 是谁散布这些有关他的流言蜚语的？', '名词: retailer 过去式: retailed 过去分词: retailed 现在分词: retailing 第三人称单数: retails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('benign', '[bɪ\'naɪn]', 'adj.仁慈的；温和的；良性的', '1. My mother\'s character is very benign. 我母亲非常慈祥。 2. The heat, the bureaucracy, the confusion and complications of his job, had reduced him in seven years to a blob of benign jelly. 炎热的天气，官僚政治和他工作的错综复杂和混乱，在七个年头里已使他变成一个仁慈的和稀泥老手。 3. The benign weather brought North America a bumper crop. 温和的气候给北美带来大丰收。 4. After tests the tumor was found to be benign. 检测发现肿瘤是良性的。', '副词: benignly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lie', '[laɪ]', 'v.躺下；位于；在于；平放；存在；延伸；说谎 n.谎言', '1. If you feel unwell, go and lie down. 如果你感到不舒服，就去躺下。 2. My home town lies low in a hidden valley. 我的家乡位于一个隐蔽的山谷里。 3. The fundamental way out lies in reform and openness. 根本出路在于改革开放。 4. The novel is lying on the table. 小说平放在桌子上。 5. He degraded himself by cheating and telling lies. 他因欺骗、撒谎而损害了自己的人格。', '过去式: lay/lied 过去分词: lain/lied 现在分词: lying 第三人称单数: lies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attribute', '[\'ætrɪbjuːt]', 'vt.把 ... 归于 n.属性；标志；象征；特征', '1. Most historians attribute such declines to wars and conquests. 大多数的历史学家把这样的衰亡归于战争和征服。 2. Many people\'s success can be attributed to hard work and a bit of luck. 很多人的成功都可以归于勤奋加上一点儿运气。 3. Public perception can also create a legal right for an attribute of a product. 公众的认知也能为产品的某个属性创造法律权利。 4. The attribute that indicates that the same copy of a routine cannot be used by another task. 一种属性，表示某一例行程序的同一副本不能被另一个任务使用。', '形容词: attributable 名词: attributer 过去式: attributed 过去分词: attributed 现在分词: attributing 第三人称单数: attributes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fourteen', '[ˌfɔːr\'tiːn]', 'num.十四', '1. She toured the U.S. when she was fourteen. 她十四岁时就在美国旅游观光。 2. My younger sister is all but fourteen years old. 我妹妹差不多十四岁了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('management', '[\'mænɪdʒmənt]', 'n.管理；管理部门；手腕', '1. The farm prospered through good management. 由于管理有方，农场兴旺发达。 2. The failure of the scheme was due to bad management. 计划的失败是由于管理不善。 3. The management took all reasonable safety precautions. 管理部门采取了一切合理的安全措施。 4. She gets them to accept these changes by tactful management. 她用机智的手段使他们接受了这些改变。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glorious', '[\'ɡlɔːriəs]', 'adj.光荣的；辉煌的；<口>愉快的', '1. She is always bucking about her glorious past. 她老是吹嘘她的光荣的过去。 2. It is a task at once glorious and arduous. 这样的任务是非常光荣的，但同时也是非常艰巨的。 3. The picture reminds me of my glorious past. 这幅画使我想起了我辉煌的过去。 4. Our country has a glorious past. 我们的国家有一段光辉的历史。', '副词: gloriously 名词: gloriousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('second', '[\'sekənd]', 'adj.第二的；次等的；再一个的 num.第二 n.片刻；秒 adv.第二；其次 v.支持；赞成；附和；调派', '1. Her beautiful roses won the second prize at the flower show. 她那些美丽的玫瑰在花展上得了二等奖。 2. Our goods are second to none in the world market. 在国际市场上,我们的商品不亚于任何人。 3. The bookcase needs a second coat of paint. 这个书柜需要再刷一层漆。 4. The train will leave in a second. 列车马上要开了。 5. Second, smoking is harmful also to your family members. 第二,吸烟也会给你的家人带来危害。 6. The motion has been seconded. 这一提议得到了支持。', '过去式: seconded 过去分词: seconded 现在分词: seconding 第三人称单数: seconds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cotton', '[\'kɑːtn]', 'n.棉花；棉制品；棉布', '1. India exports tea and cotton to many different countries. 印度向许多国家出口茶叶和棉花。 2. This district used to grow cotton on a large scale. 这个地区过去大量种棉花。 3. The import of cotton goods went up sharply in 1986. 在1986年，棉织品的进口猛增。 4. Cotton material was not known in Europe until much later. 直到很晚之后，欧洲才知道棉花布料。', '过去式: cottoned 过去分词: cottoned 现在分词: cottoning 第三人称单数: cottons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('see', '[siː]', 'v.看见；明白；了解；经历；设想 n.主教教区；主角权限', '1. If you shut your eyes you can\'t see. 要是把眼睛闭上就什么也看不见了。 2. When the sun goes down, we can see the stars. 当太阳落下,我们能看见星星。 3. It is getting dark and I cannot see to read. 天渐渐黑了,我看不见字,无法再阅读了。 4. \"The door opens like this.\"\"Oh, I see.\" “这门是这样开的。”,“噢,我明白了。” 5. The see of the pope is namely the bishop of Rome. 罗马教皇,即罗马的主教的教座。', '过去式: saw 过去分词: seen 现在分词: seeing 第三人称单数: sees');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brisk', '[brɪsk]', 'adj.敏锐的；活泼的；活跃的；轻快的；凛冽的 v.（使）轻快', '1. His movements were brisk and boyish. 他的动作仍很敏捷，孩子气。 2. He was a vigorous, brisk person. 他是一个强壮的，活泼有力的人。 3. Diana \'s brisk, commanding voice rang out from a passage way. 黛安娜活泼而威严的声音从一条过道中传了出来。 4. Trading was brisk on the Stock Exchangetoday. 今日证券交易所交投活跃。 5. He brisked up his pace at the beautiful sight. 看到那美丽的景色，他加快了脚步。', '副词: briskly 比较级: brisker 最高级: briskest 名词: briskness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lion', '[\'laɪən]', 'n.勇猛的人；狮子', '1. He is regarded as a lion. 大家认为他是个很勇猛的人。 2. The lion attacked its victim with great ferocity. 狮子凶猛地扑向猎物。 3. The lion lay asleep in its den. 狮子躺在洞里睡觉。 4. The lion seized its prey and ate it. 狮子抓住猎物，把它吃了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('judgement', '[\'dʒʌdʒmənt]', 'n.判断；判决；审判；评价；意见', '1. Her decision seems to show a lack of political judgement. 她的决定似乎显示出缺乏政治判断力。 2. Politicians should not engage in business affairs that might affect their political judgement. 政治家不应该参与那些可能会影响其政治判断力的商业事务。 3. My judgement was frequently faulty, but my loyalty to the nation could not be questioned. 我的判断经常出错，但是我对祖国的忠诚是无可置疑的。 4. The judgement passed against him. 判决宣告他败诉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('void', '[vɔɪd]', 'adj.空的；无效的；缺乏的 n.真空；空白；空虚 vt.使无效；排泄；使空出 vi.排泄', '1. Void function may not return a value 空函数不可返回一个值。 2. The court ruled that the claim was null and void. 法庭裁决此项要求无效。 3. His suggestions are totally void of common sense. 他的建议完全缺乏常识。 4. That part of the town is completely void of interest for visitors. 城镇的那部分对游客完全没有吸引力。 5. In the next weeks, government floated as in a void. 以后的几个星期,政府宛如漂浮于真空之中。 6. We will void the existing and issue a new one. 我们将把现有的作废，然后再出一张新的。', '名词: voider 过去式: voided 过去分词: voided 现在分词: voiding 第三人称单数: voids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comprehensive', '[ˌkɑːmprɪ\'hensɪv]', 'adj.全面的；广泛的；综合的；理解的', '1. The reporter has made a comprehensive report. 记者已做了全面的报道。 2. She has a comprehensive grasp of the subject. 她已全面掌握了这一学科。 3. Applying the most comprehensive metal is iron. 应用最广泛的金属是铁。 4. We have a rather comprehensive subway system here. 我们这儿有相当广泛的地铁系统。', '副词: comprehensively 名词: comprehensiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('character', '[\'kærəktər]', 'n.个性；品质；字符；人物；名誉；地位 adj.[剧](角色)代表某一特性的', '1. The boy has a strong character. 这孩子个性很强。 2. He is remembered for the nobility of his character. 他因品质高尚而被人怀念。 3. We need only keep track of the last marked character. 我们只要记住最后标记的字符。 4. I never saw a character so thoroughly hit off . 我从没看见过一个人物被描写得如此淋漓尽致。', '形容词: characterless 过去式: charactered 过去分词: charactered 现在分词: charactering 第三人称单数: characters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fit', '[fɪt]', 'adj.适宜的；合适的；健康的 v.适合；安装 n.发作；适宜', '1. I don\'t see fit to tell you all my plans. 我认为把所有的计划都告诉你是不适宜的。 2. The soil is fit for cotton planting. 这种土壤适宜种棉花。 3. The room was a fit place for study. 这个房间适宜读书。 4. He could find a fit opportunity to divulge their marriage. 他找到一个合适的机会来宣布他们的婚姻。 5. His endowments are limited, and scarcely fit him for this post. 他的天资有限,不太适合担任这项职务。 6. She had a fit of hysterics and called him some bad names. 她一阵歇斯底里发作，骂了他几句。', '副词: fitly 比较级: fitter 最高级: fittest 名词: fitter 过去式: fitted/fit 过去分词: fitted 现在分词: fitting 第三人称单数: fits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('salad', '[\'sæləd]', 'n.色拉；凉拌生菜；杂烩', '1. It only takes a minute to make a salad. 做色拉用不了多少时间。 2. I think I\'ll go for the fruit salad. 我想我还是要水果色拉吧。 3. Onions must be chopped up to make a salad. 要做凉拌菜得把洋葱剁碎。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('divert', '[daɪ\'vɜːrt]', 'v.转移；娱乐', '1. A loud noise diverted my attention. 一阵喧闹声转移了我们的注意力。 2. They diverted the river to supply water to the town. 他们使河流改道以便向城市供水。 3. She dished up the anti-pollution business to divert the attention of the public. 她把防止污染的事情说得十分重要,以便转移公众的注意。 4. I found a computer game to divert the children. 我发现了一种供孩子娱乐的电脑游戏。', '副词: divertingly 名词: diverter 过去式: diverted 过去分词: diverted 现在分词: diverting 第三人称单数: diverts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('meal', '[miːl]', 'n.一餐；膳食 n.粗碾的谷物', '1. My mother usually cooks a hot meal in the evening. 我妈妈通常在晚上煮一顿热饭。 2. This is the best meal I had ever eaten. 这是我所吃过的最好的一餐。 3. That restaurant provided us with a good meal. 饭店给我们提供了美味的膳食。 4. We can offer children the reasonable meal and the well balanced nourishment every day. 我们可以每天给孩子们提供合理的膳食和均衡的营养。 5. Meal can be made from corn and used in a wide variety of foods. 玉米粉是由玉米制成的,可以用于多种食品中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('avoid', '[ə\'vɔɪd]', 'vt.避免；逃避；[律]使无效；撤销', '1. You should avoid unnecessary repetition. 你应避免不必要的重复。 2. They all avoided mentioning that name. 他们都避免提及那名字。 3. He\'ll grab at any excuse to avoid doing the dishes. 他会随便找个借口来逃避洗碗。 4. No one can avoid his own responsibility. 没有人能够逃避自己的责任。', '形容词: avoidable 副词: avoidably 名词: avoider 过去式: avoided 过去分词: avoided 现在分词: avoiding 第三人称单数: avoids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sole', '[soʊl]', 'adj.独占的；唯一的 n.脚底；鞋底 n.鳎鱼 vt.给(鞋)换底', '1. He has the sole agency for Ford car. 他有福特汽车的独家代理权。 2. His sole motive is to make more money. 他唯一的动机就是多赚钱。 3. Farming is his sole livelihood. 他唯一的谋生之道就是务农。 4. He has pain on the sole of his feet. 他脚底很痛。 5. I\'m having my shoes soled and heeled. 我要叫人给鞋子换鞋底和鞋跟。', '名词复数: sole 过去式: soled 过去分词: soled 现在分词: soling 第三人称单数: soles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beautiful', '[\'bjuːtɪfl]', 'adj.美丽的；好的；出色的', '1. She is, as it were, the most beautiful girl I\'ve ever seen. 她可说是我见过的最漂亮的姑娘。 2. Looking at a beautiful painting always gives one satisfaction. 观赏一幅美丽的图画使人心满意足。 3. Many beautiful fish are fast disappearing because of the severe pollution. 因为污染严重，许多美丽的鱼类正在面临绝种。 4. The weather has been beautiful this week. 这星期天气一直很好。', '副词: beautifully 名词: beautifulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('artificial', '[ˌɑːrtɪ\'fɪʃl]', 'adj.人造的；虚伪的；武断的', '1. This orange drink contains no artificial flavourings. 这种橙汁饮品不含人工调味料。 2. This dress is made of artificial fibers. 这件衣服是人造纤维的。 3. She welcomed us with an artificial smile on her face. 她脸上挂着虚委的笑容来迎接我们。 4. Her artificial manner made me sick. 她那装腔作势的样子令我恶心。', '副词: artificially 名词: artificiality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lively', '[\'laɪvli]', 'adj.活泼的； 活跃的； 栩栩如生的； 真实的 adv.<废语>生机勃勃地', '1. He is an outgoing and lively person. 他是个性格开朗而又活泼的人。 2. She\'s a lively child and popular with everyone. 她是个活泼的孩子，大家都喜欢她。 3. Life on campus is friendly, safe and very lively. 校园生活是友好的，安全的和十分活跃的。 4. It was a confusing, yet lively era. 它是混乱的，也是活跃的年代。', '副词: livelily 比较级: livelier 最高级: liveliest 名词: liveliness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heavy', '[\'hevi]', 'adj.大(量)的；重的；沉重的；猛烈的', '1. As we are booking heavy orders, we would advise your order at once. 因为我方的订单量非常大,我方建议贵公司毫不犹豫地立即下订单。 2. He made efforts to move the heavy furniture. 他努力搬动沉重的家具。 3. The lead is heavy and the plastic is light. 铅是重的，而塑料是轻的。 4. We had heavy hearts as we went to a funeral. 我们怀着沉重的心情参加葬礼。', '比较级: heavier 最高级: heaviest 名词: heaviness 名词复数: heavies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tube', '[tuːb]', 'n.管子；管状物；<英>地铁；电视；管状器官 v.提供或装上管子', '1. This tube is flexible but tough. 这管子柔软但很坚固。 2. She bought a tube of toothpaste. 她买了一管牙膏。 3. I go to work on the tube. 我经常乘地铁去上班。 4. What\'s on the tube? 电视上正演什么?', '过去式: tubed 过去分词: tubed 现在分词: tubing 第三人称单数: tubes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('apple', '[\'æpl]', 'n.苹果；珍宝；家伙', '1. My uncle has an apple orchard. 我叔叔拥有一个苹果园。 2. The apple trees are blossoming. 苹果树正在开花。 3. He regard his new bike as the apple of his eye. 他把他的新自行车视为珍宝。 4. He\'s a rotten apple. 他是一个讨厌的家伙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sideways', '[\'saɪdweɪz]', 'adv.向旁边；斜着地；向侧面地 adj.旁边的；斜着；向侧面的', '1. The trees are bushing out sideways. 这些树正往四周长杈。 2. He dropped the box sideways, so it hit me. 他把箱子向旁边一扔 3. He looked sideways at me in the meeting. 他在会议上斜着眼看我。 4. They stepped sideways down the stairs. 他们侧身一步步走下楼梯。 5. Her new job is just a sideways move. 她的新工作只是平级调动。', '异体字: sideway');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bypass', '[\'baɪpɑːs]', 'vt.绕开；忽视 n.支路；旁道', '1. If we bypass the town we\'ll miss all traffic. 我们绕城外走，就不会受交通拥挤之累了。 2. If we bypass the town we\'ll miss all the traffic. 如果我们绕过市区,我们就会避开所有的车辆。 3. You cannot bypass this question. 你不能回避这个问题。 4. He bypassed his colleagues on the board and went ahead with the deal. 他未征求董事会中同事的意见就做了这笔交易。 5. If we take the bypass we\'ll avoid the town centre. 我们走旁道，就能避开市镇的中心。', '过去式: bypassed 过去分词: bypassed 现在分词: bypassing 第三人称单数: bypasses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('position', '[pə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.位置；职位；立场；状态 vt.安置；定位', '1. Can you find our position on this map? 你能在这幅地图上找到我们的位置吗? 2. I can tell the time from the position of the sun. 我可以从太阳的位置知道时刻。 3. The position of manager is still open. 经理职位仍然空缺。 4. He got the position on the strength of his skill in finance. 他凭著自己的理财本领得到了这个职位。 5. She positioned herself near the warm fire. 她待在温暖的炉子的旁边。', '形容词: positional 副词: positionally 名词: positioner 过去式: positioned 过去分词: positioned 现在分词: positioning 第三人称单数: positions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('burst', '[bɜːrst]', 'n.爆发；破裂；阵 v.爆裂；迸发；冲；闯', '1. There was a burst of laughter in the next room. 隔壁房间里突然爆发出一阵笑声。 2. The pipe burst and a spout of water shoot out. 水管破裂了，一股水喷了出来。 3. Prices went up and up in recent years, before the housing bubble burst. 最近几年价格持续上涨，直到房价泡沫的破裂。 4. I\'ve eaten so much I\'m bursting at the seams. 我吃得太多了，肚子都要撑破了。', '过去式: burst 过去分词: burst 现在分词: bursting 第三人称单数: bursts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('talent', '[\'tælənt]', 'n.天赋；才能，才艺；天才；人才；<英俚>美人', '1. He has great talent, but he has lost his faith. 他很有天赋，但是他已经丧失了信心。 2. The mother found that her son had a musical talent. 母亲发现儿子有音乐天赋。 3. Her talents are well known. 人人都知道她很有才干。 4. His talent was largely self-developed. 他的才能主要是自己培养的。', '形容词: talented 名词: talentlessness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adventure', '[əd\'ventʃər]', 'n.冒险；奇遇 vt.冒险；尝试 vi.冒险；大胆进行', '1. To the well-organized mind, death is but the next great adventure. 中文的意思是,对于一个理性极其成熟的人来说,死亡仅仅是下一个伟大冒险。 2. No matter how hard he tried, he couldn\'t persuade his friends to give up the adventure. 无论他怎么努力,都不能说服他的朋友们放弃冒险。 3. He\'s sailed the seven seas in search of adventure. 他闯荡七大洋去历险。 4. The man ventures his life in space exploration. 这个人冒着生命危险探索宇宙空间。 5. It is foolish to haphazardly adventure. 随便冒险是愚蠢的。', '过去式: adventured 过去分词: adventured 现在分词: adventuring 第三人称单数: adventures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scratch', '[skrætʃ]', 'v.抓；搔（痒）；划破；划掉 n.抓痕；乱写；抓的声音；起跑线 adj.无让步的', '1. The dog is scratching at the door. 狗正在抓门。 2. He pretended to scratch his ear. 他假装搔耳朵。 3. I had to scratch my head to remember his name. 我只想苦苦地回忆他的名字。 4. Be careful not to scratch the furniture. 小心别刮坏家具。 5. There\'s a scratch on the side of my car. 我的汽车侧面有一道划痕。', '名词: scratcher 过去式: scratched 过去分词: scratched 现在分词: scratching 第三人称单数: scratches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('regulation', '[ˌreɡju\'leɪʃn]', 'n.管理；规章；规则 adj.规定的', '1. We need the regulation of share prices. 我们需要对股票价格的管制。 2. From now on any violation of the regulation must be cruelly punished. 今后任何违反秩序的行为会受到严厉惩罚。 3. It\'s wrong of you to get around the regulation. 你存心规避规章制度是不对的。 4. This regulation refers only to children. 这些规定仅适用于儿童。 5. She was fined for driving above the regulation speed. 她因超速开车而被罚款。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rot', '[rɑːt]', 'n.腐烂；腐蚀；败坏；胡话 v.腐烂；使 ... 枯朽；消瘦', '1. Foot rot is an avoidable affiction. 烂蹄病是可以避免的。 2. Rot in the tree trunk caused the tree to fall. 树干的腐烂导致树倒了。 3. The roof timbers were affected by rot and insect attack. 屋顶的木料已经腐朽并遭虫害。 4. We should stop it the minute the rot sets in. 腐败一产生，我们就应立即制止住。 5. This cheap wine will rot your stomach. 这种劣质葡萄喝了会伤胃。', '过去式: rotted 过去分词: rotted 现在分词: rotting 第三人称单数: rots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('idle', '[\'aɪdl]', 'adj.无目的；无聊的; 懒惰的；闲散的; 无根据的 vt.虚度; 使空闲 vi.不作事；闲逛; (机器)空转', '1. Being at an idle end,we often go to and look around the shops. 闲来无事，我们常去逛逛商店。 2. Idle folks have the least leisure. 懒惰的人最没空闲。 3. No matter how rich, one shall not live an idle life. 不管一个人多么富有,都不应该过着闲散的生活。 4. I never believe idle reports. 我从来不信捕风捉影的传闻。 5. The strike idled many workers. 罢工使许多工人没事干。 6. I hate you to idle about. 我不喜欢你游手好闲。', '副词: idly 比较级: idler 最高级: idlest 名词: idleness 过去式: idled 过去分词: idled 现在分词: idling 第三人称单数: idles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obedience', '[ə\'biːdiəns]', 'n.服从；顺从', '1. The slaves gave passive obedience to their master. 奴隶们乖乖地服从他们的主人。 2. He demanded obedience from his inferiors. 他要求下级服从他。 3. He put up a token show of obedience. 他装出一副顺从的样子。 4. You are attracted to obedience and warmth. 你会被顺从和温暖的感觉所吸引。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scrutiny', '[\'skruːtəni]', 'n.监视；细看；周密的调查', '1. Counting is now underway under the close scrutiny of several thousand observers. 现在,计票工作正在几千名观察员的密切监视下进行。 2. She was conscious of his scrutiny of her face. 她觉察到了他长时间的注视着她的脸。 3. The diamond passed the scrutiny of the jeweler. 钻石通过了珠宝商的仔细检查。 4. His theory wouldn\'t bear scrutiny. 他的理论经不起周密的调查。', '名词复数: scrutinies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('country', '[\'kʌntri]', 'n.国家；乡村；区域；乡村音乐 adj.乡村的；国家的；故乡的；乡村音乐的', '1. China is a developing country. 中国是一个发展中国家。 2. After many years abroad, he wanted to return home to his country. 在国外多年后，他想回到故乡。 3. The country is very green in spring. 春天的时候，乡村一片青葱碧绿。 4. She lived her whole life in the country. 她在农村度过一生。 5. After ten years in the city, he is still country. 他在城里待了十年，仍是乡气十足。', '名词复数: countries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bosom', '[\'bʊzəm]', 'n.胸部；胸怀；内部；内心 adj.亲密的；知心的 vt.拥抱；把...藏心中', '1. She clasped the baby to her bosom. 她把孩子紧紧抱在怀里。 2. Her bosom rose and fell as she breathed. 她的胸脯随着呼吸而高低起伏。 3. He bared his bosom to the crowd. 他向众人袒示胸怀。 4. She felt the cool wind unique to this valley, laden with a heavy scent of earth, caressing her bosom. 她感到河谷里特有的，那种土腥味儿很浓的凉风正拂入她的胸怀。 5. The threat of death makes bosom buddies of us all. 死亡的威胁使我们都成了亲密的伙伴。 6. Because God, too, wishes for all humankind to copy Jesus\' example and through him to be embraced in the bosom of His love, He has labored throughout the long history. 因为神也是在期待所有的人类能效法耶稣，把他当成模范，并且通过耶稣而拥抱神的爱，因为神在整个慢长的历史里，也是非常地劳苦。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arrival', '[ə\'raɪvl]', 'n.到达；达到；到达者；新生儿', '1. I am impatient for his arrival. 我渴盼着他的到来。 2. The secretary informed me of his arrival. 秘书通知我他来了。 3. Since her arrival at the company, she has re-organized several departments. 自从她到这个公司,她已经重组了几个部门了。 4. Early arrivals get all the best parking spaces. 早来的人能停到最好的停车位。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bell', '[bel]', 'n.钟；铃；门铃；钟声；钟状物 vt.敲钟；使象钟状地张开 vi.使呈钟状；张开', '1. The church bell tolled the hour. 教堂的鸣钟报时。 2. I was roused by the sound of the bell this morning. 今天早晨，我被铃声唤醒。 3. I was too preoccupied to hear the bell. 当时我出神地想着心事，没有听见门铃响。 4. The church bell calls up my wedding day. 教堂的钟声使我想起了我结婚的那天。 5. The young monk clangs the bell every morning. 年幼的和尚每天早晨当当地敲钟。 6. The thief got flurried,thinking that it was too bad to have produced the crashiing sound which would himself on the bell,trying to muffle the crashing sound with his arms. 他心里一急，身子一下子扑到了钟上，张开双臂想捂住钟声，可钟声又怎么捂得住呢！', '过去式: belled 过去分词: belled 现在分词: belling 第三人称单数: bells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('convenience', '[kən\'viːnjəns]', 'n.便利；舒适；适宜；便利设施；方便的时间', '1. It\'s a great convenience to live in town. 住在城市里有很大的方便。 2. I stock upon grocery at the convenience store. 我到便利商店买食品备用。 3. The hotel combines comfort with convenience. 这家旅馆既舒适又方便。 4. Analyzed experiment data, the best one is ultrasonic in the light of convenience, quick, especially avoid sample color disturbing and hydrargyrum pollution. 通过实验得出数据，进行分析，确定了超声法为最适宜样品前处理方法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brush', '[brʌʃ]', 'n.刷子；画笔；刷 n.灌木丛 n.小冲突；争吵 vt.刷；掠过；轻触；擦；掸 vi.轻擦；拂拭', '1. He painted the wall with a brush. 他用刷子涂墙。 2. The painter swept a brush over his canvas. 画家的画笔在画布上飞掠。 3. I\'ll give my coat a good brush. 我要把我的衣服好好刷一下。 4. Let\'s burn off the rest of the brush. 让我们把剩下的灌木丛清除掉。 5. He had a brush with his neighbour. 他和邻居发生了一点摩擦。 6. We should brush our teeth at least twice a day. 我们每天应该至少刷两次牙。 7. Don\'t bother to move.I think I can just brush past. 不必麻烦动了,我想我能擦身挤过去。', '形容词: brushy 名词: brusher 过去式: brushed 过去分词: brushed 现在分词: brushing 第三人称单数: brushes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('legend', '[\'ledʒənd]', 'n.传说；传奇；图例', '1. According to the old legend, Romulus was the founder of Rome. 按照古老的传说，罗穆卢斯是古罗马的建国者。 2. This oriental legend is fascinating. 这个东方传说很吸引人。 3. The little girl is very interested in the old legend of immortal creatures. 小女孩对有关永生的精灵的古老传奇非常感兴趣。 4. He is a legend in his lifetime for his scientific discoveries. 他的科学发现使他一生成为传奇人物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hazard', '[\'hæzərd]', 'n.危险；冒险；危害 vt.冒险；赌运气 阿扎尔（英超切尔西队球员）', '1. The car had its hazard warning lights on. 这辆汽车亮起了危险信号灯。 2. He had put his own life in hazard. 他是在拿自己的生命来冒险。 3. There are many serious health hazards associated with smoking. 许多危害健康的情况都与吸烟有关。 4. He hazarded all his money in the attempt to save the business. 他为挽救这家企业，不惜冒险投入他的全部金钱。', '过去式: hazarded 过去分词: hazarded 现在分词: hazarding 第三人称单数: hazards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('formidable', '[\'fɔːrmɪdəbl]', 'adj.强大的；可怕的；难对付的', '1. He was one of the most formidable intellects of his time. 他是该时代的盖世奇才。 2. His mother is a most formidable lady. 他的母亲是个最令人生畏的妇人。 3. They climbed up the last part of the mountain in formidable weather conditions. 他们在恶劣的天气条件下登上了山的顶峰。 4. Martin is formidable. His left hook is devastating. 马丁很难对付，他的左钩拳极有威力。', '副词: formidably 名词: formidability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shatter', '[\'ʃætər]', 'v.粉碎；毁坏；<口>使震骇；使精疲力尽 n.碎片', '1. The glass shattered. 这杯子碎了。 2. She shattered the cup when she dropped it on the floor. 她把杯子掉在地板上,摔得粉碎。 3. My dreams have been shattered. 我的梦想已经破灭了。 4. Her experience of divorce shattered her illusions about love. 她的离婚经历使她对爱情的幻想破灭了。 5. The broken vase lay in shatters. 那只打碎了的花瓶的碎片撒了一地。', '副词: shatteringly 过去式: shattered 过去分词: shattered 现在分词: shattering 第三人称单数: shatters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prolong', '[prə\'lɔːŋ]', 'vt.延长；拖延', '1. How can we endeavor to prolong the brevity of human life? 我们怎样才能延长短促的人生？ 2. The meeting may be prolonged into the evening because so many problems have to be solved tonight. 会议可能要延长到夜里，因为今晚有太多问题要解决。 3. Low leakage current helps to prolong battery life. 低漏电流有助于延长电池使用寿命。 4. Clear evidence of his intent is to prolong the ritual. 显然他意在拖延典礼时间。', '名词: prolonger 过去式: prolonged 过去分词: prolonged 现在分词: prolonging 第三人称单数: prolongs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('superstition', '[ˌsuːpər\'stɪʃn]', 'n.迷信；没有根据的理论', '1. It\'s a common superstition that black cats are unlucky. 认为黑猫不吉利，这是一种普遍的迷信思想。 2. He holds that ignorance leads to superstition. 他认为无知会导致迷信。 3. That superstition was prevalent among them. 那种迷信在他们之间广为流传。 4. The superstition still lingers on among them. 那种迷信仍然残留在他们的脑海中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('head', '[hed]', 'n.头部；头脑；顶端；领袖；硬币的正面 v.前进；为首；朝向 adj.首要的；前面的', '1. Please raise your head and look at the blackboard. 请抬起头来，看黑板。 2. The stone caught him on the side of the head. 那块石头击中他头部的侧面。 3. He had no head for business. 他毫无商业头脑。 4. We walked straight to the head of the line. 我们一直朝线路的顶端前进。 5. We are heading home. 我们正向家的方向走去。 6. My mother is the head librarian of the school library. 我的妈妈是学校图书馆管理员组长。', '过去式: headed 过去分词: headed 现在分词: heading 第三人称单数: heads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Negro', '[\'niːɡroʊ]', 'adj.黑人的 n.(含歧视意味)黑人', '1. As offering meet, the negro\'s blood? 黑人的鲜血怎能上供自由之神！ 2. For Negro poverty is not white poverty. 因为黑人的贫困不是白人的贫困。 3. He was the first Negro ever to enroll there. 他是学院招收的第一个黑人学生。 4. Music has always been important in Negro life. 音乐在黑人生活中一直占有重要地位。', '名词复数: Negroes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('itself', '[ɪt\'self]', 'pron.它自己', '1. The cat is washing itself. 猫正在给自己洗脸。 2. The government made itself unpopular. 这届政府使得自己失去人心。 3. The house itself is not particularly to my mind, but I like its environment. 这房子本身并不特别合我的心意，但我喜欢它周围的环境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rim', '[rɪm]', 'n.边；框 vt.镶边 vi.形成边缘', '1. The water was even with the rim of the basin. 盆里的水与盆边平齐了。 2. She put a flower on the rim of the hat. 她在帽子边上放了一朵花。 3. She opened the door, and the yellow light from inside rimmed about her. 她打开门，里面射出的灯光在她的身影四周镶了一圈黄色的边。 4. The ball hit the rim and bounced off. 球击中篮框边缘并弹开了。 5. Trees rimmed the pool. 池塘边长了一圈树。 6. She opened the door, and the yellow light from inside rimmed about her. 她打开门，里面射出的灯光在她的身影四周镶了一圈黄色的边。', '过去式: rimmed 过去分词: rimmed 现在分词: rimming 第三人称单数: rims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('target', '[\'tɑːrɡɪt]', 'n.目标；对象；靶 vt.把 ... 作为目标；瞄准', '1. The sights of the gun must be in alignment with the target. 枪的瞄准器必须与射击目标对准成一线。 2. The shot was way off target. 这次射得远离目标。 3. A stationary target is easiest to aim at. 静止的目标是最容易瞄准的。 4. The company has met their export target. 该公司已经实现了它们的出口目标。 5. In the future, the Group will target its marketing and promotional activities to reach the mass of customers through cost effective means. 展望未来,集团将在具成本效益的情况下,以市场推广及宣传活动为目标,把九方推广至广大消费者。', '过去式: targeted 过去分词: targeted 现在分词: targeting 第三人称单数: targets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mirror', '[\'mɪrər]', 'n.镜子；反映 vt.反映；反射', '1. Steam has fogged the bathroom mirror. 水蒸气把浴室里的镜子遮住了。 2. A glance in the mirror reassured him that his tie wasn\'t crooked. 他照了一下镜子，领带确实没有戴歪。 3. She stared at herself in the mirror. 她凝视着镜中的自己。 4. The clear water mirrored the blue sky. 清澈的水中映出蔚蓝的天空。', '过去式: mirrored 过去分词: mirrored 现在分词: mirroring 第三人称单数: mirrors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weak', '[wiːk]', 'adj.弱的；虚弱的；无力的；差的；淡薄的', '1. The troops were too weak to withstand. 军队太弱了,抵挡不住下一次进攻。 2. The small weak child became the scorn of the class. 这个瘦小软弱的孩子成为全班嘲笑的对象。 3. He was too weak even to lift his hand. 他虚弱得连手都抬不起来。 4. She felt weak from lack of sleep. 她由于睡眠不足感到浑身无力。', '比较级: weaker 最高级: weakest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('behavior', '[bɪ\'heɪvjə]', 'n.行为；举止；习性；态度', '1. His behavior was, in a word, shocking. 总之，他的行为是令人震惊的。 2. His behavior called forth sharp criticism. 他的行为招致尖锐的批评。 3. His strange behavior made the police suspicious. 他不寻常的举止引起了警察的怀疑。 4. Their behavior towards me shows that they do not like me. 他们对我的举止说明他们不喜欢我。', '形容词: behavioral 副词: behaviorally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('greet', '[ɡriːt]', 'vt.迎接；问候；致敬；作出反应', '1. I greet you in the name of the President. 我代表总统前来迎接您。 2. He greeted her with a loving hug. 他以一个深情的拥抱来迎接她。 3. They greet each other with a hug and say Merry Christmas! 他们互相拥抱,互相问候圣诞快乐! 4. Mick greeted her with a kiss on each cheek. 米克亲吻她的双颊以表问候。', '名词: greeter 过去式: greeted 过去分词: greeted 现在分词: greeting 第三人称单数: greets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cereal', '[\'sɪriəl]', 'n.麦片粥；谷类食物 adj.谷类的；谷物的', '1. He sprinkled sugar over his cereal. 他在麦片粥里撒上了糖。 2. I have a bowl of cereal every morning. 我每天早晨吃一碗麦片粥。 3. The breakfast cereal is enriched with vitamins. 维生素增加了早餐谷类食物的营养价值。 4. The disease attacks cereal crop. 这种疾病侵害了谷类作物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aeroplane', '[\'erəpleɪn]', 'n.飞机', '1. We took a flight in an aeroplane. 我们乘飞机飞行。 2. He flew the aeroplane over to France. 他驾驶飞机来到法国。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hamburger', '[\'hæmbɜːrɡər]', 'n.汉堡包', '1. She ordered a hamburger and French fries. 她叫了一客汉堡包和炸薯条。 2. I had a hamburger and a fried chicken leg. 我吃一个汉堡包，一个炸鸡腿。 3. Don\'t always eat hamburgers for meals, or else you\'ll get malnourished. 别总把汉堡包当饭吃，不然你会营养不良的。', '异体字: hamburg');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('depart', '[dɪ\'pɑːrt]', 'vt.离开 vi.离开；死亡', '1. He departed this life at the age of seventy. 他70岁时去世。 2. I\'ll depart Washington for London tomorrow 我明天将离开华盛顿前往伦敦。 3. He seemed somewhat loath to depart. 他似乎不愿离去。 4. The train to Beijing will depart from platform 3 in half an hour. 开往北京的火车将于半小时后从三站台开出。', '过去式: departed 过去分词: departed 现在分词: departing 第三人称单数: departs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gasoline', '[\'ɡæsəliːn]', 'n.<美>汽油 亦写作gasolene', '1. The car is short of gasoline. 汽车的汽油不够了。 2. Our gasoline has been used up. 我们的汽油用完了。 3. Gasoline drained slowly from the tilted can. 煤油慢慢从倾斜的油罐里流出来 4. The plant converts crude oil into gasoline. 这家工厂将原油加工成汽油。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('striking', '[\'straɪkɪŋ]', 'adj.显著的；吸引人的 动词strike的现在分词形式.', '1. Visually, the decor was very striking. 这个房间的装饰看上去非常醒目。 2. Her big eyes are her most striking feature. 大眼睛是她容貌最显著的特点。 3. What is immediately striking is how resourceful the children are. 最令人注目的是孩子们的机智聪明。', '副词: strikingly 名词: strikingness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sweet', '[swiːt]', 'adj.甜的；芳香的；悦耳的；漂亮的 n.甜食；糖', '1. Do you like sweet or dry sherry? 你喜欢甜的还是不甜的雪利酒? 2. The dish tastes a bit sweet. 这菜有点儿甜味。 3. Don\'t the roses smell sweet! 这玫瑰花真香! 4. The soprano\'s voice sounded clear and sweet. 那女高音歌手的嗓音响亮而动听。 5. You can have some more sweet. 你可以再吃点儿甜食。', '副词: sweetly 比较级: sweeter 最高级: sweetest 名词: sweetness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('applaud', '[ə\'plɔːd]', 'vi.拍手喝彩 vt.称赞；赞成；鼓掌', '1. He leaped to his feet and began to applaud. 他跳起来开始鼓掌。 2. Please don\'t applaud until everyone has performed. 请在每个人表演完毕后再鼓掌。 3. Should I applaud my husband or chastise him? 我是该称赞还是责罚我的丈夫呢？ 4. Before I begin to flame anything, I would like to applaud a few folks. 在我开始对任何事激动之前,我想称赞一些人。', '形容词: applaudable 副词: applaudably 名词: applauder 过去式: applauded 过去分词: applauded 现在分词: applauding 第三人称单数: applauds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bowel', '[\'baʊəl]', 'n.肠；内部', '1. Do you have a bowel movement today? 你今天上过厕所吗？ 2. Her bowel will engorge quite often, I\'m afraid. 她的肠将会经常充血,我害怕。 3. He had cancer of bowel. 他得了肠癌。 4. What is it like in the bowels of the earth? 地球内部是什么样子？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jungle', '[\'dʒʌŋɡl]', 'adj.丛林的；垃圾的 n.丛林；密林', '1. We should have cut away the jungle brush. 我们本应该把丛林的灌木砍掉。 2. This jungle juice will knock you for a loop. 你喝了这种烈酒会醉倒的。 3. There\'s not much jungle 100 miles inland. 向内地100英里处丛林较少。 4. The new road was hacked out of the jungle. 这条新路是在丛林地带开辟出来的。', '形容词: jungly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('darling', '[\'dɑːrlɪŋ]', 'n.亲爱的；可爱的人；可爱的物 adj.可爱的；亲爱的', '1. Do you know where I have put my keys,darling? 你知道我的钥匙放在什么地方吗，亲爱的？ 2. Darling, please select a good mount for me. 亲爱的，请帮我挑选一匹好马。 3. I learned that Ruben was a darling man who bought from everyone. 我了解到鲁本是一个可爱的人，不管谁上门拉广告他都会来者不拒。 4. I learned that Ruben was a darling man who bought from everyone. 我了解到鲁本是一个可爱的人，不管谁上门拉广告他都会来者不拒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bounce', '[baʊns]', 'vi.弹起；重新恢复；退票 vt.使弹起；解雇；驱逐 n.弹跳；弹力；活力', '1. The ball hit the wall and bounced off it. 球打在墙上又反弹回来。 2. She\'s had many misfortunes in her life but she always bounces back. 她一生中经历过许多挫折，然而总是能重新振作起来。 3. He is young enough to bounce back from this disappointment. 他很年轻，能够从这次挫折中恢复过来。 4. I hope this cheque doesn\'t bounce. 我希望这张支票别遭退票 5. I bounced the baby on my knee. 我把婴儿放在膝上上下颠着。 6. The volleyball gave a high bounce. 排球高高地弹起来。', '过去式: bounced 过去分词: bounced 现在分词: bouncing 第三人称单数: bounces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pride', '[praɪd]', 'n.骄傲；自豪；自尊心；引以自豪的东西 vt.以 ... 自豪', '1. My teaching is my pride and joy. 我的教学工作是我的快乐和骄傲。 2. Pride was his downfall. 骄傲是他垮台的原因。 3. She takes great pride in her children\'s success. 她为自己的孩子取得的成绩感到无比骄傲。 4. He looked at his children with evident pride. 他看着自己的孩子,充满自豪。 5. He prides himself on remaining calm in an emergency. 他在紧急关头十分镇静为此感到骄傲。', '过去式: prided 过去分词: prided 现在分词: priding 第三人称单数: prides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seldom', '[\'seldəm]', 'adv.很少；难得', '1. He seldom eats breakfast. 他很少吃早餐。 2. The apple tree is seldom fruitful. 这棵苹果树很少结果。 3. I have seldom seen such brutality. 我很少见到这种暴行。 4. We go out very seldom. 我们绝少外出。', '名词: seldomness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pigeon', '[\'pɪdʒɪn]', 'n.鸽子', '1. A pigeon perched on our porch railing. 一只鸽子栖息在我们门廊的栏杆上。 2. Little pigeon can carry great message. 鸽子虽小，大事可传。 3. A pigeon is cooing up in one of the elm. 一只鸽子在榆树上咕咕地叫。 4. An old man sat on the park bench and fed the pigeon. 一位老人坐在公园的长凳上喂鸽子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('imperative', '[ɪm\'perətɪv]', 'adj.紧要的；必要的；祈使的 n.紧要的事；命令；义务；驱使', '1. It is imperative that we make a quick decision. 我们要尽快做出决定。 2. It\'s imperative that you apologize to him immediately. 你必须立即向他道歉。 3. \"Go!\" is in the imperative mood. “Go！”是祈使语气的句子。 4. Survival is our first imperative. 我们当务之急是设法生存下来。', '副词: imperatively 名词: imperativeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fox', '[fɑːks]', 'n.狐狸；狡猾的人；<美>迷人的时髦女郎 vt.欺骗；迷惑', '1. The fox lay dying in a pool of gore. 狐狸倒在血泊中奄奄一息。 2. The fox went to ground under a rocky escarpment. 狐狸钻进了石崖下面的洞里。 3. He\'s a crafty old fox. 他是一只狡猾的老狐狸。 4. Don\'t trust him, he is a sly old fox. 别相信他，他像老狐狸一样狡猾。 5. The trainee foxed the arrogant instructor with a knotty problem. 那位受训的队员故意用难题把傲慢的教练搞糊涂。', '名词复数: foxes 过去式: foxed 过去分词: foxed 现在分词: foxing 第三人称单数: foxes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sneak', '[sniːk]', 'vt.偷偷摸摸做 vi.偷偷地走；偷偷地做 n.鬼鬼祟祟的人；潜行；溜 adj.出其不意的；暗中进行的', '1. He sneaked a chocolate from the box. 他从盒子里偷拿了一块巧克力。 2. I\'ll see if I can sneak him in after dark. 我看天黑后能否让他偷偷地溜进去。 3. I can sneak you out without being noticed. 我能把你偷偷地带出去，别人了现不了。 4. The cat ate the food and sneaked off. 猫吃完食物就偷偷跑了。 5. The sneak who took our lunch spoiled our picnic. 那个鬼鬼祟祟偷走了我们午饭的人，破坏了我们的野餐。 6. This sneak raid was very successful. We took the enemy leader captive. 这次偷袭非常成功，活捉了敌酋。', '过去式: sneaked/snuck 过去分词: sneaked/snuck 现在分词: sneaking 第三人称单数: sneaks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interface', '[\'ɪntərfeɪs]', 'n.界面；接口 v.连接；作接口', '1. You cannot have more than one interface with the same name. 您不能对多个网络接口使用相同的名字。 2. Can you give me an explanation of the man-machine interface? 你能给我解释一下人机接口吗？ 3. Our office microcomputers interface with the mainframe computer in London. 我们办公室的微机与伦敦总机相连接。', '形容词: interfacial 过去式: interfaced 过去分词: interfaced 现在分词: interfacing 第三人称单数: interfaces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seem', '[siːm]', 'vi.似乎；好像', '1. He seems to know everything. 他似乎什么都懂。 2. The children seem unaffected emotionally by their parent\'s divorce. 孩子在情绪上似乎未受到父母离婚的影响。 3. Well, funny things seem to be happening. 哦,似乎有些怪事正在不断发生。 4. I\'m sorry, I seem to have mislaid my ticket. 对不起,我的车票好像弄丢了。', '过去式: seemed 过去分词: seemed 现在分词: seeming 第三人称单数: seems');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('perfume', '[pər\'fjuːm]', 'n.香水；香气 vt.洒香水于；使香气弥漫', '1. The room reeked of cheap perfume. 房间里弥漫著劣质香水的呛鼻气味。 2. The smell of her perfume lingered in the empty house. 空屋里仍然飘溢著她的香水味。 3. A mist of perfume hung in the air. 空气中飘溢著香水的雾气。 4. Can you smell the perfume of the roses? 你能闻到玫瑰花的香味吗？ 5. She perfumed herself with Eau de Cologne. 她身上洒著古龙水。', '过去式: perfumed 过去分词: perfumed 现在分词: perfuming 第三人称单数: perfumes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disorder', '[dɪs\'ɔːrdər]', 'n.混乱；杂乱；不适；失调；疾病 vt.扰乱', '1. The meeting terminated in disorder. 会议在混乱中结束。 2. This school is completely in disorder. 这所学校完全在混乱状态当中。 3. The whole country of Hungary is in disorder right now. 整个匈牙利现在陷入了一片混乱。 4. The room is in dreadful disorder. 房间里乱七八糟。 5. A series of accidents disordered the shop. 一连串的意外事件把店里弄得乱七八糟。', '过去式: disordered 过去分词: disordered 现在分词: disordering 第三人称单数: disorders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('headmaster', '[ˌhed\'mæstər]', 'n.(中小学的)校长', '1. The headmaster patted the pupil on the shoulder. 校长轻轻拍拍那个学生的肩膀。 2. My father is a headmaster of a primary school. 我父亲是小学校长。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('motive', '[\'moʊtɪv]', 'n.动机；目的；主题 adj.发动的；运动的；动机的 vt.促使', '1. Her prime motive was personal ambition. 她的主要动机是为了实现个人的志向。 2. I don\'t understand what his motive is. 我不知道他的动机是什么。 3. The police have excluded robbery as a motive for the murder. 警方已排除该谋杀案中有抢劫的动机。 4. Can we assign jealousy as the motive for the crime? 我们能否确定这一犯罪动机是出于嫉妒? 5. The water provides the motive power that turns the mill wheel. 水提供了转动轮子的动力。 6. According to the order,Communist Jiang San motived the mass to fight against the Japanese army.they eradicated the enemy,and killed his brother Jiang Er,who was a traitor. 共产党员蒋三奉命加家乡发动群众开展武装斗争，最后消灭了当地日伪军，除掉汉奸，其兄蒋二。', '过去式: motived 过去分词: motived 现在分词: motiving 第三人称单数: motives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('folk', '[foʊk]', 'n.人们；（某类或来自某个地方的）人；双亲；<口>大伙儿；民间音乐 adj.民间的', '1. A lot of folks are upset at the changes. 许多人对这些变化感到不安。 2. This is no place for young folk. 这可不是年轻人该去的地方。 3. The town folk know him as Mr. Dickey. 镇上的人们都知道他是迪基先生。 4. I\'d like you to meet my folks. 我想要你见见我的父母。 5. Chicken soup is a popular folk remedy for the common cold. 鸡汤是一种广为流传的治疗普通感冒的民间药方。', '名词复数: folk');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('explanation', '[ˌeksplə\'neɪʃn]', 'n.解释；说明', '1. I made a full and frank explanation to the court. 我对堂上直话直说,从头到尾解释了一番。 2. What did he say in explanation of his stupid behavior? 他说了什么来解释他那愚蠢的行为？ 3. There could be some psychological explanation for his bad health. 他的健康不佳可能有心理上的原因。 4. That\'s not an adequate explanation. 这并不足以说明问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thunder', '[\'θʌndər]', 'n.雷；雷声 v.打雷；轰隆地响；大声喊出', '1. Thunder always comes after lightning. 雷经常出现在闪电之后。 2. The thunder rumbled in the distance. 远处雷声隆隆。 3. We could hear the thunder of distant guns. 我们可以听到远处炮声隆隆。 4. My little dog always hides under the bed when it thunders. 我的小狗一听到打雷就藏到床底下。', '名词: thunderer 过去式: thundered 过去分词: thundered 现在分词: thundering 第三人称单数: thunders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lobby', '[\'lɑːbi]', 'n.大厅；民众接待厅；游说议员者 v.游说', '1. I waited for her in the lobby of theatre yesterday. 昨天我在戏院的大厅等她。 2. The film star held court in the hotel lobby. 这位电影明星在旅馆的大厅里接见了影迷。 3. The anti-nuclear lobby is becoming stronger. 向议员游说的反核群众声势渐强。 4. The group tried to lobby the bill through. 这个集团企图通过游说议员通过该项法案。', '名词: lobbyer 名词复数: lobbies 过去式: lobbied 过去分词: lobbied 现在分词: lobbying 第三人称单数: lobbies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rate', '[reɪt]', 'n.比率；速度；价格；费用；等级 v.认为；估价；定等级；值得；怒斥；责骂', '1. House price is rising at a higher rate than inflation. 房价比通货膨胀上涨的比率高。 2. The birth rate is the number of births compared to the number of the people. 出生率是出生数与人口数的比率。 3. Prices keep rising at a dizzy rate. 物价以极快的速度不断上涨。 4. What is the advertising rate in your newspaper? 你们报纸的广告价格是多少? 5. The novel was rated a brilliant performance. 这部小说被认为是一部出色的作品。', '过去式: rated 过去分词: rated 现在分词: rating 第三人称单数: rates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spine', '[spaɪn]', 'n.脊柱；脊椎；书脊；尖刺', '1. His spine developed a slight curve. 他的脊柱有点弯曲。 2. He got an injury to his spine when he fell off his horse. 他从马上摔下来，伤了脊梁骨。 3. Crimp spine on pages for permanent binding. 用装订机装订好书脊。 4. A little red cover with a broken spine. 那书有一个红红的封面和破败的书脊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dignity', '[\'dɪɡnəti]', 'n.尊严；高贵；端庄', '1. He would do nothing beneath his dignity. 他决不愿意干任何有损自身尊严的事。 2. The real dignity of a man lies in what he is, not in what he has. 一个人的真正尊严在于他的品格，而非他的财富。 3. A man\'s dignity depends not upon his wealth but upon his character. 人高尚与否不取决於他的财富,而取决於他的品格。 4. She bears herself with dignity. 她举止庄重大方。', '名词复数: dignities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('charity', '[\'tʃærəti]', 'n.慈善；宽厚；慈善机关(团体)；仁慈', '1. They did so under the mask of charity. 他们是打着慈善的幌子这么做的。 2. True charity doesn\'t consist in almsgiving. 真正的慈善不在于施舍。 3. She was always very generous in her charity. 她行善时总是很慷慨。 4. She regards his moral faults with charity. 她宽恕他的品行不端。', '名词复数: charities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quest', '[kwest]', 'n.探索；寻求 v.寻找；搜索', '1. This fruitless quest was called alchemy by the Arabs. 这种无谓的的探索被阿拉伯人称作炼金术。 2. Man will suffer many disappointments in his quest for truth. 人类在探索真理过程中必然会遭受挫折。 3. The quest for gold was difficult. 寻找金矿是很困难的。 4. The lawyer was on a quest for further evidence. 律师正在到处找寻更多的证据。 5. He decided to go on and continue with his quest. 他决定继续前进，继续寻找问题的答案。', '名词: quester 过去式: quested 过去分词: quested 现在分词: questing 第三人称单数: quests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('person', '[\'pɜːrsn]', 'n.人；本人；身体', '1. You are just the person I want to see. 你正是我要见的人。 2. He is a very nice person to work with. 他是一个很好共事的人。 3. Every person is accountable for his own work. 每个人都要对自己的工作负责。 4. The firm has an important asset in the person of the director of research. 公司有一巨大财富，就是研究部主任这个人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contrast', '[\'kɑːntræst]', 'n.对比；差别；对照物 v.对比；成对照 n.[计算机] 反差', '1. Black and white shows a striking contrast. 黑和白形成明显的对比。 2. There is a great contrast between good and evil. 善与恶有明显的差别。 3. The little village was a total contrast to San Francisco. 这个小村庄与圣弗朗西斯科形成强烈对照。 4. When you contrast their work records, Julie is clearly more qualified. 对比他们的工作记录,你会发现茱莉更有能力。 5. The microscope image contains contrast effects. 显微镜所成的图像具有反差效应。', '形容词: contrastable 副词: contrastingly 过去式: contrasted 过去分词: contrasted 现在分词: contrasting 第三人称单数: contrasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('creep', '[kriːp]', 'vi.蹑手蹑脚地走；爬；渐渐出现；蔓延；毛骨悚然 n.卑鄙小人；爬；徐行；蠕动', '1. We take off our shoes and creep cautiously along the passage. 我们脱掉了鞋，在走廊中蹑手蹑脚地往前走。 2. The spider learns to creep on the wall. 蜘蛛学爬壁。 3. As the doctors became more tired, errors began to creep into their work. 由于越来越疲劳，医生的工作开始出现差错。 4. Old age creeps up on you before you realize it. 人不知不觉就变老了。 5. You slimy little creep! 你这个卑鄙无耻的奴才！', '过去式: crept 过去分词: crept 现在分词: creeping 第三人称单数: creeps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('end', '[end]', 'n.结束；末端；目标；死亡；部分；终点站；端点；半边球场；剩余物，残余；过世 v.终止，结束', '1. The battle finally brought the war to an end. 这一仗使这场战争终告结束。 2. At the end of the film, the hero wept bitterly. 在影片的结尾，主人公伤心地哭了。 3. He makes a knot in the end of the string. 他在绳子末端打了个结。 4. He could have achieved his ends by peaceful means. 他要是采用和平手段的话就会完成他的目标。 5. The debate ended in uproar. 那场争辩以大吵大闹收场。', '过去式: ended 过去分词: ended 现在分词: ending 第三人称单数: ends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flour', '[\'flaʊər]', 'n.面粉；粉末 v.研成粉末；撒上粉', '1. Bread is chiefly made of flour. 面包主要是由面粉做成的。 2. He used a miller to mill the grain into flour. 他用碾磨机把谷物磨成面粉。 3. In the flour mill, wheat grains are powdered. 麦粒在磨坊被磨成粉末。 4. The surface of the road was like brown flour, very fine powder, and it was surprisingly slippery stuff. 表面的道路就像布朗面粉，非常细的粉末，这是令人惊讶的湿滑的东西。 5. You may flour the pastry board so that the dough doesn\'t stick to it. 你可以在做糕点的面板上撒些面粉，这样揉好的面粉就不会粘到板上了。', '形容词: floury 过去式: floured 过去分词: floured 现在分词: flouring 第三人称单数: flours');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thrill', '[θrɪl]', 'n.激动；引起激动的事物；震颤（医学） v.(使)激动；感到紧张', '1. It gave me a real thrill to see her again after so many years. 那么多年后与她重逢,我非常激动。 2. With a thrill I realized that I had won. 我意识到自己获得了胜利 3. It was a real thrill to meet the Queen. 能见到女王的确是令人兴奋的事。 4. Hester looked at him with a thrill of another joy. 海丝特望着他，心头又是一阵喜悦的震颤。 5. It\'s a sight that never fails to thrill me. 那是一种永远让我激动不已的景象。', '副词: thrillingly 过去式: thrilled 过去分词: thrilled 现在分词: thrilling 第三人称单数: thrills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('decay', '[dɪ\'keɪ]', 'v.(使)衰退；(使)腐败；(使)腐烂 n.衰退；腐烂；腐败', '1. Naomi: Your entire body is begining to decay. 直美:你的整个身体都在衰退。 2. What made the Roman Empire decay? 罗马帝国为何衰亡？ 3. The dampness of the climate decayed the books. 气候潮湿，把书都霉坏了。 4. The vegetables have begun to decay. 那些蔬菜已开始腐烂。 5. His mental decay is distressing. 他的智力衰退令人苦恼。', '名词: decayer 过去式: decayed 过去分词: decayed 现在分词: decaying 第三人称单数: decays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stoop', '[stuːp]', 'n.佝偻；弯腰；屈尊；俯冲 v.弯腰；屈服；佝偻；屈尊；降格；俯冲', '1. The old woman walked with a stoop. 老太太伛偻而行。 2. Try not to walk with such a stoop. 尽量不要驼着背走路。 3. She has always walked with a stoop. 她总是弯腰走路。 4. The hawk descend in a vertical stoop on its quarry. 鹰向它的猎物直冲而下。 5. She stooped low to look under the bed. 她弯下腰看床底下。', '过去式: stooped 过去分词: stooped 现在分词: stooping 第三人称单数: stoops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('specialize', '[\'speʃəlaɪz]', 'v.专攻', '1. This shop specializes in chocolates. 这个商店专门出售巧克力。 2. He specializes in oriental history. 他专门研究东方史。 3. I specialize in the sale of cotton piece goods. May I act as your agent? 我专营棉布买卖，我可作为你们的代理吗？ 4. \"A science fiction cannot not be regarded as a mere entertainment, but in fact it tells the reader much more.\" \"科幻小说不能简单地看成是供消遣的，而实际上它给读者展示更深刻的内容。\"', '过去式: specialized 过去分词: specialized 现在分词: specializing 第三人称单数: specializes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arrive', '[ə\'raɪv]', 'vi.到达；到来；成功', '1. We shall arrive soon after. 我们将很快就到达。 2. You must arrive at the airport two hours early. 你必须提前两小时到达机场。 3. The great day has arrived. 伟大的日子已经到来。 4. The baby finally arrived just after midnight. 婴儿终於在刚过午夜时候降生了.', '名词: arriver 过去式: arrived 过去分词: arrived 现在分词: arriving 第三人称单数: arrives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('represent', '[ˌreprɪ\'zent]', 'vt.表现；表示；描绘；代表；象征；说明；阐明 vi.提出异议', '1. Monsters in dreams often represent fears. 怪物在梦里经常表现为恐惧。 2. Both represent the triumph of passion over reason. 两者都表现出理智之外的激情。 3. Dotted arrows represent flow of information. 虚矢线表示信息流程。 4. You must represent your complaints to Head Office. 你必须向总部表示出你的抱怨。', '形容词: representable 名词: representability 过去式: represented 过去分词: represented 现在分词: representing 第三人称单数: represents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chase', '[tʃeɪs]', 'vt.追捕；追求；镂刻，雕刻；试图赢得 vi.奔跑；追赶 n.追捕；争取；狩猎', '1. Chase the cow out of the garden. 把牛逐出花园。 2. He chased (after) the burglar but couldn\'t catch him. 他追赶窃贼却未捉住。 3. Why do modern people chase material possessions? 为什么现在的人们追求物质财富？ 4. The criminal was caught after a car chase. 开着汽车追来追去才把罪犯捉住。', '过去式: chased 过去分词: chased 现在分词: chasing 第三人称单数: chases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yesterday', '[\'jestərdeɪ]', 'n.昨天；近来 adv.昨天；近来', '1. Yesterday was Friday. 昨天是星期五。 2. I saw him only yesterday. 我昨天才见到他。 3. She had an attack of indigestion yesterday. 她昨天消化不良。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('polar', '[\'poʊlər]', 'adj.两极的；对立的 n.极线；极性', '1. Are there any animals in the polar circles? 南极圈和北极圈内有动物存在吗？ 2. The two systems of government are polar opposites. 这两种政体正好相反。 3. The two systems of government are polar opposites. 这两种政体正好相反。 4. Love and hatred are polar feelings. 爱与恨是完全相反的感情。 5. A molecule where the centers do not coincide is called a polar molecule. 正负电荷中心不重合的分子称为极性分子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('torment', '[\'tɔːrment]', 'n.苦痛；拷问；折磨；烦恼 vt.使苦恼；折磨', '1. He was in torment after the operation. 手术后他非常痛苦。 2. That child is a torment to his parents. 这孩子对他的父母是一种折磨。 3. He suffered a hideous torment when the enemy caught him. 敌人抓到他后，他受到可怕的折磨。 4. What a little torment that child is! 这孩子真烦人！ 5. She torments everyone with silly questions. 她用无聊的问题来烦扰大家。', '副词: tormentingly 过去式: tormented 过去分词: tormented 现在分词: tormenting 第三人称单数: torments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('motel', '[moʊ\'tel]', 'n.汽车旅馆', '1. I went back to the motel to phone Jane. 我回到汽车旅馆给珍打电话。 2. The motel is dead ahead about a mile from here. 那家汽车旅馆就在前方大约一英里的地方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gown', '[ɡaʊn]', 'n.长袍；长外衣', '1. She is in a purplish mantle, pink gown. 她身穿一件紫色披肩，桃红色长袍。 2. She wore a black silk evening gown. 她穿着一件黑色丝质晚礼服。 3. She put on her silken gown before going to bed. 睡觉前，她穿上丝质的睡衣。 4. She wore an antique gown to the costume party. 她穿着一件过时的长袍参加化妆舞会。', '过去式: gowned 过去分词: gowned 现在分词: gowning 第三人称单数: gowns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('numerical', '[nuː\'merɪkl]', 'adj.数字的；用数字表示的', '1. Budgeting is the formulation of plans for a given future period in numerical terms. 预算是用数字的形式来表示将来某一确定期间的计划。 2. This includes text, numerical calculations, mathematical derivations, diagrams, graphs, computer programs, and output. 这包括本文，数字的计算，数学的引出，图表，曲线图，计算机计画和输出。 3. Hash values are unique and compact numerical representations of a piece of data. 哈希值是一块数据唯一和紧凑的数字表示形式。', '副词: numerically 异体字: numeric');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pat', '[pæt]', 'n.轻拍；轻打；小块 v.轻拍；抚摸；拍打', '1. He gave her a reassuring pat on the shoulder. 他轻拍了一下她的肩膀让她放心。 2. He gave me a light pat on the shoulder. 他在我肩上轻轻一拍。 3. It was a basket with fresh eggs, a newly-baked loaf of bread, a pat of butter. 这个篮子里有新鲜鸡蛋，一条新出炉的面包和一小块黄油。 4. The children wanted to pat the bunny . 孩子们想轻拍这只兔子。', '副词: patly 名词: patness 过去式: patted 过去分词: patted 现在分词: patting 第三人称单数: pats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('statement', '[\'steɪtmənt]', 'n.陈述；声明；【计】语句', '1. She refused to make a statement to the police lest she （should） incriminate herself. 她拒绝向警方作陈述以免受连累。 2. Her views were fully elaborated in a written statement. 她的观点在一篇书面声明中得到了充分的阐述。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hip', '[hɪp]', 'n.臀部；髋；屋脊 adj.<非>时髦的；通晓的 int.（欢呼声）嘿', '1. The needle went into my hip with a prick. 针一下刺进了我的臀部。 2. A bullet from one of the pistols had graze his hip. 有一枝手枪里发出的一颗子弹擦伤了他的臀部。 3. She fell and broke her left hip. 她摔倒了,折断了左髋关节。 4. The designer is hip to the latest fashion. 设计师对时装的最新款式了如指掌。 5. Hip, hip, hooray! 嘿，嘿，万岁!', '副词: hiply 异体字: hep 比较级: hipper/hepper 最高级: hippest/heppest 名词: hipness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('serial', '[\'sɪriəl]', 'n.连载小说；序列；连续剧 adj.连续的；一系列的', '1. After breakfast, he went on with his serial. 早饭之后,他继续写他的连载故事。 2. Downloaded serial numbers may not be transferred. 下载的序列号不能传输。 3. Please write down your serial number. 请记录下您的序列号。 4. Most of her novels have been made into television serials at some time. 同时她的多数小说拍成了电视连续剧。 5. Currency notes have serial number. 钞票上有连续的号码。', '副词: serially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('entitle', '[ɪn\'taɪtl]', 'vt.取名为；使有权利', '1. She read a poem entitled The Apple Tree. 她读了一首题为《苹果树》的诗。 2. He entitled the book Savage Love. 他给这本书取名为《野性的爱》。 3. His services entitle him to our respect. 凭他的功劳他应受我们尊敬。 4. Your qualifications entitle you to a higher salary. 你的资格使你有权享有较高的薪水。', '名词: entitlement 过去式: entitled 过去分词: entitled 现在分词: entitling 第三人称单数: entitles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('native', '[\'neɪtɪv]', 'adj.本国的；本土的；当地的 n.土著；本地人；本国人', '1. He\'s emigrated to the USA and gone completely native. 他已移居美国，完全成了美国人。 2. My native language is Chinese. 我的母语是汉语。 3. You can tell from his blue eyes that he isn\'t native to China. 你可以从他的蓝眼睛看出他不是中国本土的人。 4. I have often been asked why I am not adopting a Native American. 别人经常问我为什么不领养美国本土的孩子。 5. The kangaroo is a native of Australia. 袋鼠是产于澳大利亚的动物。', '副词: natively 名词: nativeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('retrieve', '[rɪ\'triːv]', 'vt.恢复；挽回；取回 vi.找回猎物 n.恢复；取回；救出险球', '1. The company is fighting to retrieve its market share. 这个公司正在为恢复其市场份额(占有率)而奋斗。 2. She tried to retrieve the situation by making profuse apologies. 她不住的道歉,力图挽回局面。 3. I should like to retrieve my umbrella which I left in the car. 我想取回我留在车上忘记带走的雨伞。 4. The dog is trained to retrieve. 这狗受过训能找到并带回猎物。 5. This is a loss beyond retrieve. 这是无可挽回的损失。', '形容词: retrievable 副词: retrievably 名词: retrievability 过去式: retrieved 过去分词: retrieved 现在分词: retrieving 第三人称单数: retrieves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hay', '[heɪ]', 'n.干草；<俚>一小笔钱；床', '1. The children snuggled down on the hay. 孩子们舒适地蜷伏在干草上。 2. Make hay while the sun shines. [谚]把握时机；趁热打铁。 3. The men hit the hay early, in order to be out hunting at dawn. 为了第二天破晓出去打猎，这些人很早就上床睡觉了。', '名词: hayer 过去式: hayed 过去分词: hayed 现在分词: haying 第三人称单数: hays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tone', '[toʊn]', 'n.语气；音调；调子；色调；风气 v.使更健壮；定调；调色；装腔作势地说', '1. He often speaks in an arrogant tone. 他经常以一种傲慢的口气说话。 2. I dislike his airy tone of voice. 我讨厌他那做作的声调。 3. That violin has a beautiful tone. 那支小提琴的音色很美。 4. The tone of the meeting was pleasant and innocuous. 会见的调子是令人愉快和坦率的。 5. Swimming is the best way to tone up your body . 游泳是强身健体的最佳途径。', '过去式: toned 过去分词: toned 现在分词: toning 第三人称单数: tones');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('butter', '[\'bʌtər]', 'n.黄油；奶油 vt.涂黄油；奉承', '1. inflict symbolically 2. My mother asked me to cream the butter and sugar together. 妈妈让我把黄油和糖搅成奶油状。 3. She cooks omelets in butter as they do in France. 她用奶油做法国式的蛋卷。 4. She filmed a slice of bread with butter. 她涂一层薄薄的奶油在一片面包上。 5. I\'ll butter the bread. 我会给面包涂上黄油。', '过去式: buttered 过去分词: buttered 现在分词: buttering 第三人称单数: butters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('partial', '[\'pɑːrʃl]', 'adj.不完全的；部分的；偏袒的；偏爱的', '1. around three 2. The research project was only a partial success. 那个研究课题只取得部分成功。 3. You will receive some partial credit even you don\'t finish it. 如果你没作完的话,你还是可以得到部分的分数。 4. His partial attitude called forth a lot of criticism. 他的偏袒态度招致了不少批评。', '名词: partialness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pound', '[paʊnd]', 'n.磅；英镑 n.（汽车）扣押所；宠物收留所 vt.捣碎；敲打；连续猛击 vi.咚咚地走；怦怦地响', '1. I lost several pounds last month. 我上个月瘦了好几磅。 2. The shop is selling choice apple, so I buy 3 pound. 那商店在卖上选苹果,所以我买了三磅。 3. There is a 1 pound admission charge. 入场费为1英镑。 4. I paid him b pound , and he gave me 20 pence change. 我付了一英镑 5. Have you redeemed your car from the pound? 你有没有取回被扣的汽车? 6. The farmers pound rice in a mortar. 农民们在臼中舂米。 7. Do not pound up the stairs! 上楼梯不要跺脚！', '名词: pounder 名词复数: pound 过去式: pounded 过去分词: pounded 现在分词: pounding 第三人称单数: pounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cope', '[koʊp]', 'vi.应付；对抗；妥善处理 vt.笼罩；盖上斗篷 n.长袍；斗篷状物', '1. He was scarcely able to cope with the situation. 他几乎不知道如何去应付这个局面。 2. I don\'t know how she copes with looking after her family and doing a full-time job. 既要照顾家庭又要全天工作，我不知道她是如何对付的。 3. No one could cope with him in debate. 没人能同他在辩论中对抗。 4. I cannot cope with such a pile of work. 我无法处理这么多工作。 5. The cope of clouds covering the city cleared up by mid-day. 笼罩城市的厚重乌云在中午时散开了。 6. The judge was wearing a black cope. 这位法官穿著一件黑色的法衣。', '名词: coper 过去式: coped 过去分词: coped 现在分词: coping 第三人称单数: copes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mouse', '[maʊs]', 'n.老鼠；胆小如鼠的人；鼠标 v.捕鼠；仔细搜寻；移动鼠标至...之上', '1. The mouse scurried into its hole when the cat appeared. 猫一露面，老鼠急忙钻进自己的洞里。 2. The cat is playing with a live mouse. 猫在戏弄那只活老鼠。 3. He remained a mouse in public affairs. 在公众事务上他依然胆小如鼠。 4. My mouse is broken, so I need to get a new one. 我的鼠标坏了，得去买个新的。 5. Does your cat mouse well? 你家的猫很会抓老鼠吗?', '名词复数: mice 过去式: moused 过去分词: moused 现在分词: mousing 第三人称单数: mouses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eliminate', '[ɪ\'lɪmɪneɪt]', 'v.除去；剔除；忽略；淘汰', '1. You must eliminate an unknown quantity. 你必须消去一个未知数。 2. Let us eliminate all uncertain on thought. 让我们从思想上消除一切疑惑。 3. We must eliminate unnecessary steps and get directly to the point. 我们必须忽略不必要的步骤,直接切入主题。 4. Their team was eliminated in the first round. 他们队在第一轮就被淘汰了。', '形容词: eliminative 名词: elimination 过去式: eliminated 过去分词: eliminated 现在分词: eliminating 第三人称单数: eliminates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('far', '[fɑːr]', 'adv.远；(时间)久远；很；非常；远远；进展程度 adj.较远的；最远的；远方的 n.远方', '1. The new music teacher lives far away. 新来的音乐教师住得很远。 2. How far do you make it to the station? 你估计到车站有多远? 3. I was born in a village not far from Beijing. 我出生在离北京不远的村庄里。 4. It happened far back in the past. 这事发生在久远的过去。 5. I saw her on the far side of the road. 我看见她在马路对面。 6. She sits there gazing at the far, with tears on her face. 她坐着凝视着远方，泪流满面。', '比较级: farther/further 最高级: farthest/furthest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pass', '[pæs]', 'v.通过；经过；度过；传递；发生 n.通行证；及格；乘车券；传球；关隘，山口', '1. The bill passed and became law. 议案通过后成了法律。 2. I passed the store on my way to the library. 我在去图书馆的路上经过了那家商店。 3. Where did you pass the vacation? 你在什么地方度过假期的？ 4. Pass the salt, please. 请递给我盐瓶。 5. A sergeant asked the stranger to show his pass. 警官要求这个陌生人出示通行证。', '名词: passer 过去式: passed 过去分词: passed 现在分词: passing 第三人称单数: passes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sponge', '[spʌndʒ]', 'n.海绵 vt.用海绵擦拭；吸收掉；抹掉', '1. The sponge soaked in the water on the desk. 海绵将书桌上的水吸了进去。 2. That child soaks up new facts like a sponge! 那孩子吸收新知识像海绵似的。 3. I like to sponge myself down in a hot bath. 洗热水澡时我喜欢用海绵擦洗全身。 4. Sponge the mud spots off the car. 用海绵擦去车上的污泥。', '过去式: sponged 过去分词: sponged 现在分词: sponging 第三人称单数: sponges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('therapy', '[\'θerəpi]', 'n.疗法；治疗', '1. The scraping therapy is very popular in China. 在中国刮痧疗法很受欢迎。 2. Physical therapy alternates with chemical. 理疗和化疗交替进行。 3. She was in therapy. 她正在接受治疗。 4. Self-help is an important element in therapy for the handicapped. 伤残人士在治疗中，自助自立是个重要因素。', '名词复数: therapies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('explore', '[ɪk\'splɔːr]', 'v.探测；探险；考察；探究', '1. The experts are exploring every part of the island. 专家们正在勘查这个岛的各个部分。 2. He had an itch to get away and explore. 他等不及要动身去探险。 3. Can you explore the market possibility for us? 您能为我们考察一下市场前景吗？ 4. Columbus discovered America but did not explore the new continent. 哥伦布发现了美洲', '过去式: explored 过去分词: explored 现在分词: exploring 第三人称单数: explores 名词: exploration');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('star', '[stɑːr]', 'n.星；明星 v.以星状物装饰；变成演员', '1. A lonely star shone out against the black sky. 一颗孤星在黑色的夜空中闪闪发亮。 2. This star is not visible to the naked eye. 这颗星肉眼看不见。 3. The opera star wanted in her later years. 那位歌剧明星晚年生活困苦。 4. Her ambition was to become a film star. 她一心追求的是做电影明星。 5. The cast of the play included a international star. 这个剧的演员名单中有一位国际明星。', '过去式: starred 过去分词: starred 现在分词: starring 第三人称单数: stars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('steam', '[stiːm]', 'n.蒸汽；水汽；蒸汽动力；轮船 v.蒸；冒热气；行驶；<口>发怒', '1. The engines are driven by steam. 这些发动机是由蒸汽驱动的。 2. There was a puff of steam from the engine before it stopped. 机车喷出一股蒸气后就停了下来。 3. Steam has fogged the bathroom mirror. 水蒸气把浴室里的镜子遮住了。 4. The equipment was originally powered by steam. 这个机器最初使用蒸汽动力。 5. The car windows steamed up. 汽车窗户上有一层水汽。', '过去式: steamed 过去分词: steamed 现在分词: steaming 第三人称单数: steams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('likely', '[\'laɪkli]', 'adj.可能的；可信的 adv.很可能', '1. I\'m likely to be very busy tomorrow. 明天我可能很忙。 2. They\'ll very likely ask for an increase in the budget. 他们很可能会要求增加预算。 3. I\'ve heard whispers that the firm is likely to go bankrupt. 我听到传闻说公司很可能要破产。 4. A rather different fate seems more likely. 另一种大不相同的命运似乎更可信。 5. Most likely it were in the lining of my coat. 那东西很可能在我上衣的衬层里。', '比较级: likelier 最高级: likeliest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('damp', '[dæmp]', 'adj.潮湿的；有湿气的；沮丧的 n.湿气；潮湿 vt.使潮湿；使扫兴 vi.变潮湿', '1. Damp wood doesn\'t burn well. 潮湿的木头不好烧。 2. The building was cold and damp. 这房子又冷又湿。 3. The cheese molded in the damp cellar. 乳酪在潮湿的地下室中长了霉。 4. The party was a bit of a damp squib. 这次聚会有些扫兴。 5. The air of this room is impregnated with damp. 这房间充满着湿气。 6. Damp the cloth before you clean the windows. 在擦玻璃窗之前,把揩布弄湿。 7. Nothing could damp down my passion. 任何事情都不能磨灭我的激情。', '形容词: dampish 副词: damply 比较级: damper 最高级: dampest 名词: dampness 过去式: damped 过去分词: damped 现在分词: damping 第三人称单数: damps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Easter', '[\'iːstər]', 'n.复活节', '1. Christmas and Easter are Christian festivals. 圣诞节和复活节是基督教的节日。 2. Easter comes early this year. 今年复活节来得早。 3. At Easter, attendances at church rose. 复活节期间，到教堂做礼拜的人多了。 4. Each of my cousins received an Easter egg on Easter Day. 我的表兄弟们每人在复活节都得到了一枚复活节彩蛋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fantasy', '[\'fæntəsi]', 'n.幻想 v.幻想', '1. The young always live in a world of fantasy. 年轻人总是生活在幻想中。 2. He is unable to divorce fantasy from reality. 他不能将幻想与现实分开。 3. He fantasies himself a doctor. 他想像自己是一位医生。', '名词复数: fantasies 过去式: fantasied 过去分词: fantasied 现在分词: fantasying 第三人称单数: fantasies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nevertheless', '[ˌnevərðə\'les]', 'adv.尽管如此；不过；仍然 conj.然而；不过', '1. Our defeat was expected；nevertheless，it was disappointing. 我们的失败是意料中的事；尽管如此,还是令人失望。 2. We can\'t take your advice. Nevertheless, thank you for putting it. 我们不能接受您的建议。不过,谢谢您提出来。 3. Despite his injured ankle, he nevertheless succeeded in gaining the final against Germany. 尽管踝骨受伤,他仍然打入了与德国队的决赛。 4. Nevertheless as an exceptional measure, we have decided to overlook its late submission. 然而,作为一项特别措施,我们决定不计较逾期问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bond', '[bɑːnd]', 'n.债券；结合；协定；联系；情谊；黏合剂 vt.使结合；为 ... 作保 vi.连结；粘合', '1. An industrial firm issues bond to collect money and will pay back with interest. 工厂发行债券集资并偿还利息。 2. Marriage should be a permanent bond. 婚姻应该是永恒的结合。 3. We entered into a solemn bond. 我们缔结了一项正式协定。 4. Common interests formed a bond between us. 共同的利益把我们联系在一起。 5. The company refused to bond a former criminal. 这家公司拒绝为一个前科罪犯作保。 6. I use water resistant adhesive to get the best bond possible. 我使用防水粘合剂，以获得最佳连结性。', '形容词: bondable 名词: bonder 过去式: bonded 过去分词: bonded 现在分词: bonding 第三人称单数: bonds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('huddle', '[\'hʌdl]', 'n.杂乱一团；混乱；拥挤 v.推挤；乱堆；草率了事', '1. He shouted into the cavernous arena as if he were shouting into a huddle. 他对着球场吼叫，似乎他面对的是混乱的人群。 2. James insisted the Cavs needed to go bigger and broke from the huddle shaking his head in disagreement. 詹姆斯不住地摇头表示反对，他坚持认为骑士应该换上大个球员，打破场上的混乱局面。 3. The track led them to a huddle of barns and outbuildings. 那条路把他们带到了一片杂乱拥挤的谷仓和库房。 4. At the BeiBei plant, women huddle over a conveyor belt in frigid temperatures, gluing rubber sneakers together. 在贝贝公司，妇女拥挤在寒冷的传送带周围粘橡胶旅游鞋。', '名词: huddler 过去式: huddled 过去分词: huddled 现在分词: huddling 第三人称单数: huddles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('steamer', '[\'stiːmər]', 'n.汽船；轮船；蒸笼；[动]沙海螂', '1. The steamer arrived in harbor last night. 汽船是昨晚进港的。 2. The steamer sails for twenty miles an hour . 汽船每小时航行20英里。 3. I cannot help worrying to hear that there is no steamer this week. 我听到本周没有汽船的消息，禁不住担忧起来。 4. We\'ll ship the goods at an early time as long as there is a steamer. 只要有船，我们就尽早装货。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('asleep', '[ə\'sliːp]', 'adj.睡着的；已死的；不活跃的；麻木的 adv.睡着；进入静止状态', '1. The lion lay asleep in its den. 狮子躺在洞里睡觉。 2. He soon fell asleep with weariness. 他疲倦地很快就睡着了。 3. Some people grind their teeth while they are asleep. 有些人睡觉时磨牙齿。 4. My grandfather was asleep forever. 我的祖父过世了。 5. The fat guy dropped asleep shortly after the film began. 电影开始不久,那个胖子就睡着了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ballet', '[\'bæleɪ]', 'n.芭蕾舞', '1. He did a sketch of the ballet dancers. 他为这些芭蕾舞者画了一张素描。 2. She invited us to see the ballet. 她邀请我们去看芭蕾舞。', '形容词: balletic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bicycle', '[\'baɪsɪkl]', 'n.自行车 vi.骑自行车', '1. Can you ride a bicycle? 你会骑自行车吗？ 2. He beguiled me into lending him my bicycle. 他骗我把自行车借给了他。 3. Every day he rode his old bicycle to his office. 每天他骑着他那辆旧自行车去上班。 4. You can coast downhill on a bicycle. 你可以骑自行车滑下坡。', '名词: bicycler 过去式: bicycled 过去分词: bicycled 现在分词: bicycling 第三人称单数: bicycles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('content', '[\'kɑːntent]', 'n. 内容； 目录； 含量 adj. 满足的； 满意的 vt. 使 ... 满足； 使 ... 安心', '1. Teaching content should be concise. 教学内容要少而精。 2. The book is rich in content and succinct in style. 这本书内容丰富，文字简练。 3. Define content sections of status reports. 定义状态报告的目录部分。 4. Using file shares that provide only a hierarchical directory structure as a means of organizing content. 将只提供一个层次目录结构的文件共享作为内容组织方式使用。 5. We\'re also in the content business. 我们是也在满足的生意方面。 6. Disport oneself to one\'s heart\'s content. 玩个痛快什么也不会使他满足。', '过去式: contented 过去分词: contented 现在分词: contenting 第三人称单数: contents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disturb', '[dɪ\'stɜːrb]', 'v.扰乱；妨碍；使 ... 不安；打破...的平静；打乱...的治安', '1. They took the phone off the hook so no calls would disturb them. 他们摘下电话听筒，以免电话打扰他们。 2. I am sorry to disturb you. 很抱歉我妨碍到你了。 3. Ministers declared themselves profoundly disturbed by the violence. 大臣们自称因为暴力而感到深刻的不安。 4. A soft breeze gently disturbed the surface of the pool. 一阵微风吹拂了平静的池塘。', '副词: disturbingly 名词: disturber 过去式: disturbed 过去分词: disturbed 现在分词: disturbing 第三人称单数: disturbs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hit', '[hɪt]', 'vi.打（击）；袭击；达到 vt.要求；打（击）；碰撞；偶然发现；符合 n.讽刺；打（击）；冲撞；成功', '1. The ball hits against the wall. 球撞到了墙上。 2. She hits at him. 她朝他打去。 3. His career reached a new high with the hit song. 该首大热歌曲助他的歌唱事业达到一个新的高峰。 4. User has hit the runaway recall limit. 用户已达到超越撤回界限。 5. Don\'t hit him up for anything else but breakfast. 除了早饭外，甭向他提出别的啥子要求。 6. That last remark was a hit at me. 最后的话是对我的讽刺。', '形容词: hitless 过去式: hit 过去分词: hit 现在分词: hitting 第三人称单数: hits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glare', '[ɡler]', 'n.闪耀光；刺眼 v.发眩光；瞪视', '1. I like turning a corner from the shade of a house into the full torrid glare of an open space. 我喜欢将来自房子的色度的一个角落变成开着空间的完整晒焦的闪耀光。 2. These sunglasses are designed to reduce glare. 这些太阳镜是为减少刺眼的强光而设计的。 3. The glare of the oncoming headlights temporarily blinded me. 迎面车灯刺眼的光照得我瞬间什么也看不见。 4. Eyelashes defend the eye by shading it from glare. 眼睫毛通过遮掩眼睛而使眼睛避免受眩光刺激。', '过去式: glared 过去分词: glared 现在分词: glaring 第三人称单数: glares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discount', '[\'dɪskaʊnt]', 'n.折扣；贴现率 vt.打折扣；贴现；不全信；不重视 vi.贴现；减息贷款', '1. These goods will be sold at a discount. 这些货物将减价出售。 2. We give 10 percent discount for cash. 现金付款，我们九折优惠。 3. The discount rate is set by the Fed. 贴现率是由联储决定的。 4. The preferred project in this case depends on the discount rate, not the IRR. 该例中，我们倾向选择哪个项目取决于贴现率，而不是内部收益率。 5. That store does not discount at all. 那家商店出售商品一概不打折。 6. We usually only discount acceptance trade and commercial bills. 我们通常只贴现已承兑的商业票据。', '形容词: discountable 过去式: discounted 过去分词: discounted 现在分词: discounting 第三人称单数: discounts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('innovation', '[ˌɪnə\'veɪʃn]', 'n.创新；革新', '1. There is no end to practice or innovation. 实践永无止境,创新永无止境。 2. In the age of global competition, design innovation is vital. 在全球激烈竞争的时代,设计创新至关重要。 3. It was a period of innovation. 这是革新时期。 4. A surge of innovation in techniques is on the horizon. 技术改进的浪潮即将出现。', '形容词: innovational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mark', '[mɑːrk]', 'n.记号；痕迹；分数；商标 v.弄污；打分；留意；做标记', '1. The trade mark is an intangible asset of every enterprise. 商标是企业的一项无形资产。 2. A recorder pen makes a mark on a chart. 记录器的笔在记录卡上划一个记号。 3. War has left its mark on the country. 战争给该国留下了不可磨灭的痕迹。 4. After degating only a small witness mark remains. 浇口切除后只留下细小痕迹。 5. They have got a pile of exam papers to mark. 他们有一大堆试卷要打分。', '过去式: marked 过去分词: marked 现在分词: marking 第三人称单数: marks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ant', '[ænt]', 'n.蚂蚁', '1. Afterwards I allowed an ant to visit them. 我于是让一只蚂蚁去接近它们。 2. A dove heard the ant and flew over to help. 一只鸽子听到蚂蚁的呼救声就飞过去救它。 3. An ant will sacrifice himself for his friends. 每只蚂蚁都愿意为了朋友牺牲自己. 4. Ant is the most popular animal in the world. 蚂蚁是世界上分布最广、数量最多的生物之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('condemn', '[kən\'dem]', 'vt.谴责；判刑', '1. We must not condemn her on pure supposition. 我们不能单凭猜测就谴责她。 2. We condemn all sorts of slanders. 我们谴责一切诽谤中伤的言论。 3. Most people are willing to condemn violence. 大部分的人极力谴责暴力。 4. The criminal was condemned to death. 这个罪犯被判死刑。', '形容词: condemnable 名词: condemner 过去式: condemned 过去分词: condemned 现在分词: condemning 第三人称单数: condemns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tolerance', '[\'tɑːlərəns]', 'n.宽容；忍耐力；容忍；公差', '1. Tolerance is another name for indifference. 宽容是不关心的别名。 2. My tolerance of your impoliteness is limited. 我对你的无礼的忍耐是有限的。 3. Human beings have limited tolerance of noise. 人类对噪音的忍耐力有限。 4. She had no tolerance for jokes of any kind. 她容不得开任何玩笑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('escort', '[\'eskɔːrt]', 'n.护送者；护航舰；陪伴者；陪游；妓女 vt.护送；陪伴', '1. He offered to be her escort, but she declined it. 他提出护送她，但她谢绝了。 2. The government provided an armed escort for the visiting head of State. 政府为到访的元首派出了武装卫队。 3. He is the commander in chief of this escort ,and he holds great power. 他是这艘护航舰的总指挥，权利很大。 4. The Queen\'s yacht had an escort of ten destroyers. 有十艘驱逐舰为女王的游艇护航. 5. He will escort you through the forest. 他护送你穿过森林。', '过去式: escorted 过去分词: escorted 现在分词: escorting 第三人称单数: escorts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fact', '[fækt]', 'n.事实；真相；实际', '1. This is an objective fact no one can deny. 这是谁也无法否认的客观事实。 2. Before we make detailed plans, we need some more facts and figures. 我们需要更多的事实和数据才能制定出详细的计划。 3. I can find out the truth of the fact. 我能查出事实的真相。 4. I think you are withholding the fact from me. 我知道你对我隐瞒了事实真相。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obstruction', '[əb\'strʌkʃn]', 'n.障碍；妨碍；闭塞；违例阻挡', '1. The road was cleared from obstruction . 那条路已被清除了障碍。 2. The traffic flowed round the obstruction. 车辆绕过障碍行驶。 3. He was arrested for obstruction of a police officer in the execution of his duty. 他因妨碍警察执行公务而被逮捕。 4. These tumors often resulted in stenosis or obstruction of the bronchus. 邻近支气管常有狭窄或闭塞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('worst', '[wɜːrst]', 'adj.最坏的；最差的；最不利的 n.最坏的事物 adv.最坏；最差 形容词bad或ill的最高级.', '1. That was the worst airline disaster in history. 那是历史上最严重的空难。 2. I\'ve seen bad work,but this is the worst. 我见过做得很差的工作，但这是最差的。 3. I think the guards in this city are the worst. 我认为这城市的卫兵是最差的。 4. It is a worst psychological moment for him. 目前是敌人心理上最不利的时刻。 5. Hope for the best, but prepare for the worst. 抱最好的愿望，做最坏的打算。 6. It\'s the old and the poor who suffer worst when subsidies are cut. 补助津贴一削减，最吃苦头的就是那些老人和贫民。', '过去式: worsted 过去分词: worsted 现在分词: worsting 第三人称单数: worsts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('twelve', '[twelv]', 'num.十二', '1. She often puts in twelve hours\' work a day. 她常常一天工作十二小时 2. How old are you? I am twelve (years old). 你几岁？我十二岁。 3. The clock struck at twelve o\'clock sharp. 钟在整十二点钟打点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('passive', '[\'pæsɪv]', 'adj.被动的；消极的 n.被动性', '1. He played a passive role in the marriage. 他在婚姻中扮演了一个被动的角色。 2. You are passive when you allow things to happen, but do nothing. 当你让这些事发生,而不做任何事来阻止它,你是消极的。 3. Good is the passive that obeys reason. 善是服从理智的被动性。 4. Passive tear suctioning force can be demonstrated by a Venturi tube model. 被动性泪液吸引之力量，可藉由文氏管模型来解释。', '副词: passively 名词: passiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('memorial', '[mə\'mɔːriəl]', 'n.纪念碑；纪念物；纪念仪式 adj.纪念的；追悼的', '1. This memorial commemorates those who died in the war. 这座纪念碑是纪念战争中牺牲者的。 2. The site of the memorial is granted in perpetuity to Canada. 纪念馆址已选定在加拿大作为永久的纪念。 3. People came to the memorial to revere the memory of the great leader. 人们来到纪念馆崇敬地纪念这位伟大的领袖。 4. His memorial was engraved on the stone. 纪念他的碑文刻在石碑上。 5. He made an entry of the memorial events in his diary. 他将可纪念的大事记入日记中。', '副词: memorially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overlook', '[ˌoʊvər\'lʊk]', 'v.俯瞰；远眺；没注意到；忽视 n.忽视；远眺', '1. My room overlooked the garden. 我的房间俯瞰花园。 2. We overlook the church from our house. 我们可从家中俯瞰教堂。 3. My room overlooks the sea. 从我的房间可眺望大海。 4. He overlooked a spelling error on the first page. 他没有看出第一页中有个拼写错误。 5. It was a slight overlook on my part. 这是我的小疏忽。', '过去式: overlooked 过去分词: overlooked 现在分词: overlooking 第三人称单数: overlooks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('experiment', '[ɪk\'sperɪmənt]', 'n.试验；实验；尝试 vi.尝试；做实验', '1. The researchers are repeating the experiment on rats. 研究人员用老鼠反覆做该试验。 2. The students will have an experiment in the laboratory tomorrow. 学生们明天要在实验室里做实验。 3. Fortunately, these folks love to experiment. 幸运的是，你们喜欢尝试。 4. With Multiple Level Undo you can safely experiment with various what-if scenarios. 使用多级撤消可以安全地尝试各种假设分析方案。 5. Small businesses are anxious to experiment with computers. 小型企业都急于试用计算机。', '名词: experimenter 过去式: experimented 过去分词: experimented 现在分词: experimenting 第三人称单数: experiments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forum', '[\'fɔːrəm]', 'n.讨论会；论坛', '1. This is a forum for education and technology. 这是一个有关教育和技术的讨论会。 2. I believe that this is the key issue of the Forum. 我相信,这个问题正是这次研讨会的要旨所在。 3. The letters page of this newspaper is a forum for public argument. 这份报纸的读者来信栏是公众意见的论坛。 4. Wonderful! I put it to the English forum. 太好了!我转到英文论坛去。', '名词复数: forums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('catch', '[kætʃ]', 'v.赶上；抓住；捕捉；领会 n.捕捉；捕获物；陷阱', '1. We\'re just in time to catch the train. 我们正好赶上了火车。 2. The police are tracking down him and hope to catch him soon. 警察正在搜捕他并希望能很快抓住他。 3. It is natural for a cat to catch mice. 猫捉老鼠是本能。 4. I don\'t catch your meaning. 我不明白你的意思。 5. That\'s a nice catch. 那球接得好。', '形容词: catchable 过去式: caught 过去分词: caught 现在分词: catching 第三人称单数: catches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intersection', '[ˌɪntər\'sekʃn]', 'n.交集；十字路口；交叉点', '1. The basic algorithm for arriving at the final, applicable set of permissions is to compute the intersection of all. 最后得到的一组适用权限的算法是要计算所有权限的交集。 2. Do not use multiple aliases for a single table in the same query to simulate index intersection. 不要在同一查询中为一个表使用多个别名来模拟索引交集。 3. Breastworks were thrown up at major intersections. 在主要的十字路口都匆匆筑起了胸墙。 4. Cut to the left at the next intersection. 在下一个十字路口向左急转', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('circulate', '[\'sɜːrkjəleɪt]', 'vi.流通；循环；传播 vt.使流通，使环流', '1. Please open a window to allow the air to circulate. 打开窗子让空气流通。 2. Foreign money is not allowed to circulate in China. 外币不允许在中国流通。 3. Money shall circulate freely within the common market. 货币应在共同市场内自由流通。 4. Blood circulates through the body. 血液在体内循环。', '形容词: circulative 名词: circulator 过去式: circulated 过去分词: circulated 现在分词: circulating 第三人称单数: circulates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('album', '[\'ælbəm]', 'n.唱片集；唱片；相册；集邮册；纪念册', '1. This is one of the songs from her latest album. 这是她最新歌集里的一首歌。 2. The album contains many memorable songs. 这张唱片中包括许多值得收集的歌曲。 3. My album of boyhood photographs often reminds me of the past happiness. 童年时的相册经常让我想起儿时的欢乐。　 4. I see her put stamps in an album. 我看见她在把邮票放进集邮本去。', '名词复数: albums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('steady', '[\'stedi]', 'adj.稳定的；稳固的；坚定的 v.使稳固；使稳定；(变得)稳固；使坚定 adv.稳定地，稳固地 n. 关系固定的情侣；固定支架', '1. The old man is not steady on his legs. 这位老人站不稳。 2. The agreement ensured a steady supply of oil. 该协定保证了石油的稳定供给。 3. Don\'t tell your secret to him before you get a steady relationship. 在未跟他的感情稳定下来之前,不要把自己的秘密说给他听。 4. I know she is steady in her purpose. 我知道她意志坚定。 5. She held onto a strap to steady herself. 她抓住拉手吊带以便站稳。', '副词: steadily 比较级: steadier 最高级: steadiest 名词: steadiness 名词复数: steadies 过去式: steadied 过去分词: steadied 现在分词: steadying 第三人称单数: steadies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('know', '[noʊ]', 'v.了解；知道；认识 n.知情', '1. What do you know about us? 你对我们有什么了解? 2. I didn\'t know the truth until she told me what happened. 直到她告诉我发生的事,我才了解真相。 3. I know what happened. 我知道发生了什么事。 4. Excuse me, do you know how to play chess? 请问,你知道怎么下国际象棋吗? 5. Somebody in the know told me he\'s going to resign. 有知情者告诉我他要辞职了。', '形容词: knowable 名词: knower 过去式: knew 过去分词: known 现在分词: knowing 第三人称单数: knows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('porter', '[\'pɔːrtər]', 'n.搬运工；（列车）服务员；杂务工 n.门卫 n.<旧>黑啤酒 Porter n.波特(人名)', '1. Did you remember to tip the porter? 你记得给搬运工小费了吗？ 2. The porter will carry your luggage to your room. 搬运工会把你的行李搬到你的房间去的。 3. The porter was weighed down by all the luggage. 搬运工扛着这些行李压得直不起腰来。 4. The porter ushered us into the waiting room. 服务员把我们引进了候车室。 5. The hotel porter will call a taxi for you. 旅馆的门卫可以给你叫计程车。 6. I had forgotten all about Mr. Porter. 我已经把波特先生忘得一干二净了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rake', '[reɪk]', 'n.耙子；耙状物 n.放荡的人 n.斜度；倾角 v.用耙子聚；收集；搜索 v.使倾斜', '1. With an ancient, rusty rake I went to work. 我拿了把古老的生锈的耙子去耙叶子。 2. He was notorious as a gambler and rake. 他是声名狼藉的赌徒和浪荡子。 3. The rake of the theater floor is a bit too steep. 剧场的地板斜度太大了一点。 4. The motorcycle has an extreme rake to the front wheel. 摩托车的前轮有个最大的倾角。 5. Rake the leaves and heap them by the garage . 用耙子把叶子收在一起堆在汽车库旁边。', '名词: raker 过去式: raked 过去分词: raked 现在分词: raking 第三人称单数: rakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sector', '[\'sektər]', 'n.部门；部分；区域 n.[计]扇形；扇区 vt.使分成部分', '1. perceive superficially 2. The government made an investigation of the employment in the public and private sectors. 政府对国营和私营部门的就业情况作了一次调查。 3. Fashion is one sector of the beauty industry. 时装是美容行业的一个部分。 4. We must be careful not to confuse a segment and a sector. 我们必须小心不要把细分市场和部分市场混淆。 5. A sector of a cylindrical capacitor may thus be utilized as an energy filter. 柱面扇形电容器可作为能量过滤器。', '形容词: sectorial 过去式: sectored 过去分词: sectored 现在分词: sectoring 第三人称单数: sectors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thorough', '[\'θɜːroʊ]', 'adj.彻底的；完全的；详尽的；细致深入的', '1. I gave the radio a thorough inspection before buying it. 我把收音机彻底检查了一遍才买了下来。 2. We are trying to get a thorough understanding of the government\'s fiscal policy. 我们正努力对政府的财政政策进行全面的了解。 3. She underwent a thorough examination at the hospital. 她在医院里接受了全面检查。 4. We gave our room a thorough cleaning the next day. 第二天,我们彻底地打扫了房间。', '副词: thoroughly 名词: thoroughness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commit', '[kə\'mɪt]', 'v.犯罪；承诺；委托；托付', '1. They committed outrages on innocent citizens. 他们对无辜的市民犯下了暴行。 2. He committed suicide rather than sell out to the enemy. 他宁愿自杀而没有向敌人投降。 3. He didn\'t commit himself to anything. 他没有作任何承诺。 4. The girl was committed to the care of an aunt. 这女孩被交给姨母照顾。', '形容词: committable 过去式: committed 过去分词: committed 现在分词: committing 第三人称单数: commits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('classic', '[\'klæsɪk]', 'n.杰作；古典作品；第一流艺术家 adj.最优秀的；传统的；古典的', '1. \"War and Peace\" is a literary classic. 《战争与和平》是一部经典文学著作。 2. The idea of a classic is historically bound up with the view. 从历史上来看，古典的想法和这个观点有着密切的联系。 3. This is a really classic French champagne. 这确实是上等的法国香槟酒。 4. The novel is regarded as one of the classic works. 这篇小说被公认为是最优秀的作品之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Thursday', '[\'θɜːrzdeɪ]', 'n.星期四', '1. I\'m usually free between Tuesday and Thursday. 我通常在星期二至星期四有空。 2. The meeting is scheduled for Thursday. 会议定于星期四举行。 3. She\'s due to arrive on Thursday. Meanwhile, what do we do? 她预定星期四到达. 4. The Brethren hold a prayer meeting every Thursday. 教友每周四举行一次祷告会。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('legislation', '[ˌledʒɪs\'leɪʃn]', 'n.法律；法规；立法', '1. The new legislation is highly discriminatory. 新的法案，有许多地方厚此薄彼。 2. We protect the interests of investors by the legislation in effect. 我们根据现行法律保护投资者的利益。 3. The legislation was made retrospective. 该项法规具有追溯效力。 4. The government will introduce legislation to restrict the sale of firearms. 政府将制定法规限制枪支出售。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('torrent', '[\'tɔːrənt]', 'n.激流；山洪；(谩骂、质问等的)连发，爆发', '1. The river was a torrent after the storm. 暴风雨过后，河水成了激流。 2. The torrent scoured a gully down the hillside. 那激流顺山坡而下冲出一条水沟。 3. A torrent of water poured down the mountain. 洪水从山上奔流而下。 4. She attacked him with a torrent of abuse. 她用连珠炮似的谩骂来攻击他。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bay', '[beɪ]', 'n.海湾；月桂树；隔间；犬吠；【计】机架，底板 vi.嗥叫；哀号 adj.红棕色', '1. Sunlight shimmers on the waters of the bay. 阳光在海湾的水面上闪烁。 2. We can see a magical view over the calm water of the bay from our window. 从我们的窗户里可以看到海湾里平静海水的迷人景色。 3. In the milk was a bay leaf, a few slices of onion. 牛奶中也有一片月桂树叶和几片洋葱。 4. In the library, the books on history are all kept in one bay. 在图书馆里，历史方面的书都放在同一隔间里。 5. He is baying at the moon. 他朝着月亮吠叫。 6. The bay mare is in the next stable. 旁边的马厩中有一匹红棕色马。', '过去式: bayed 过去分词: bayed 现在分词: baying 第三人称单数: bays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('your', '[jʊr]', 'adj.你的；你们的', '1. Your work falls short of my expectations. 你的工作未达到我的期望。 2. Please advise us of any change in your plan. 你们的计划倘有变更,请告诉我们。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('satisfaction', '[ˌsætɪs\'fækʃn]', 'n.满意；赔偿；乐事；妥善处理；确信', '1. Your satisfaction is guaranteed. 包你满意。 2. His face was expressive of satisfaction. 他的脸上露出满意的神情。 3. The winner beamed with satisfaction. 获胜者满意地笑了。 4. Looking at a beautiful painting always gives one satisfaction. 观赏一幅美丽的图画使人心满意足。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cricket', '[\'krɪkɪt]', 'n.板球；蟋蟀 vi.打板球', '1. A cricket team is comprised of eleven players. 一个板球队由11名队员组成。 2. The cricket match was washed out by rain. 板球比赛因天雨而取消。 3. A cricket in the house is good luck. 屋里有蟋蟀会带来好运。 4. He angrily stomped his cricket after failing the fight. 比赛失败后，他生气地踏死了他的蟋蟀。 5. I don\'t find cricket very exciting. 我觉得打板球没有劲。', '名词: cricketer 过去式: cricketed 过去分词: cricketed 现在分词: cricketing 第三人称单数: crickets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exposure', '[ɪk\'spoʊʒər]', 'n.暴露；揭露；胶片；曝光时间；(在电视、报纸等媒体上的)亮相；挨冻', '1. Exposure of the body to strong sunlight can be harmful. 身体受烈日暴晒会造成伤害。 2. Her skin was dry after exposure to the wind. 经过风吹后她的皮肤很干。 3. His election toppled down due to the exposure of his bribery. 他的竞选因为受贿被揭露而失败了。 4. How many exposures have you left? 还剩多少底片没有照？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('asset', '[\'æset]', 'n.资产；优点；有用的东西', '1. It was too early to conclude if there was an asset price bubble. 在现阶段下结论,认为出现资产价格泡沫属言之尚早。 2. Private consumption improved and asset prices rose sharply. 私人消费有所改善,资产价格更大幅攀升。 3. The tennis player\'s speed is his great asset. 那个网球运动员动作迅速，这是他的一大优势。 4. A sense of humour is a great asset for a person. 幽默感是一个人的宝贵资产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('incidentally', '[ˌɪnsɪ\'dentli]', 'adv.附带地；偶然地；顺便地', '1. Her name was just incidentally mentioned at the end of the speech. 她的名字只是在讲话最后被附带地提了一下。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resolute', '[\'rezəluːt]', 'adj.坚决的；果断的', '1. He was resolute in carrying out his plan. 他执行起计划来是非常坚决的。 2. He is a person with graceful manner and resolute action. 他是个举止文雅但行动坚决的人。 3. We must take immediate and resolute action. 我们必须采取坚决果断的行动。 4. He curbed it, I think, as a resolute rider would curb a rearing steed. 我想，他还是管住了它，就象一个果断的骑师管住一匹用后腿站立起来的骏马。', '副词: resolutely 名词: resoluteness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heaven', '[\'hevn]', 'n.天空；天堂 Heaven. n.上帝', '1. A lark is singing in the heaven. 云雀在天空中歌唱。 2. Twinkling stars are garnishry of heaven. 闪烁的星星是天空的装饰品。 3. If there\'s a heaven on earth, this is it! 人间若有天堂，非此莫属！ 4. Christians believe that Jesus ascended into Heaven. 基督徒认为耶稣升天了。 5. It was the will of Heaven. 这是天意。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('large', '[lɑːrdʒ]', 'adj.大的；大量的；大号的；广泛的 adv.夸大地；[航海]顺风地 v.狂欢作乐', '1. Shanghai is a large city. 上海是一个大城市。 2. The oceans are large bodies of water. 海洋是广大的水域。 3. The hill was surmounted with a large castle. 小山上有一座巨大的城堡。 4. The concert drew a large audience. 音乐会吸引了大量的观众。 5. He tends to talk large. 他喜欢讲大话。', '比较级: larger 最高级: largest 名词: largeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('engagement', '[ɪn\'ɡeɪdʒmənt]', 'n.约会；约定；订婚；婚约；雇用；交战；(机器零件等)啮合', '1. I have numerous engagements for next year. 我明年有许多约会。 2. Fidelity to engagement is a virtue. 信守诺言是一种美德。 3. Their engagement was announced in the papers. 他们订婚的消息登报了。 4. He broke off his engagement to her. 他对她解除了婚约。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intrinsic', '[ɪn\'trɪnsɪk]', 'adj.内在的；固有的；本质的', '1. You have a natural and intrinsic talent and skill. 你天生就具备内在的天赋和才能。 2. These difficulties are intrinsic to such a situation 这是这种情势下固然会有的困难。 3. The intrinsic worth of the pen is 30 yuan. 这支钢笔本身价值是30元。', '副词: intrinsically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('April', '[\'eɪprəl]', 'n.四月', '1. April is the time to plant trees. 四月是种树的时候。 2. The manuscript bears the date 10 April 1937. 手稿上注著1937年4月10日。 3. He moved into this house in April. 他是四月份搬进这所房子的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('complex', '[kəm\'pleks]', 'adj.复杂的；合成的；复合的 n.综合体；复合体；[医]综合症状；[心]情结', '1. It was a complex problem. 这是一个复杂的问题。 2. This enhances the complex flavors and bouquet of the wine. 这加强了酒的合成的味道。 3. Complex briary fruit with smoldering oak. 有复合的水果香和烟熏橡木香。 4. They also provide composable functionality required to support complex, large-scale systems. 并提供可复合的功能以支持复杂的大规模系统。 5. Libraries are great complexes of tiny items. 图书馆是细小类目的大综合体。', '副词: complexly 名词: complexness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rank', '[ræŋk]', 'n.等级；阶层；排；列 v.排列；分等级；列为；排名，排位 adj.繁茂的；讨厌的', '1. He is above me in rank. 他的级别比我高。 2. They are people of all ranks and classes. 他们来自各阶层各阶级。 3. Taxis stand in a taxi rank waiting to be hired. 出租汽车排成一行等人雇车。 4. The riot police quickly fell into rank for action. 防暴警察迅速列队准备行动。 5. Rank the states in the order of size. 按大小把这些州排列一下。', '副词: rankly 比较级: ranker 最高级: rankest 名词: rankness 过去式: ranked 过去分词: ranked 现在分词: ranking 第三人称单数: ranks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('symphony', '[\'sɪmfəni]', 'n.交响乐', '1. The first movement of the symphony is beautiful. 这部交响乐的第一乐章是很优美的。 2. I like listening to the symphony. 我喜欢听交响乐。', '名词复数: symphonies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pollute', '[pə\'luːt]', 'v.污染；弄脏', '1. Our store never sells books which pollute the mind. 我们书店从不出售污染心灵的书籍。 2. We should not pollute our rivers with waste. 我们不应让废弃物污染我们的河川。', '名词: polluter 过去式: polluted 过去分词: polluted 现在分词: polluting 第三人称单数: pollutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obstruct', '[əb\'strʌkt]', 'v.阻隔；妨碍；阻塞', '1. They do not obstruct most individuals who use patented products. 他们不会妨碍个人使用专利产品。 2. Five colors bewilder our eyes and obstruct our insights. 五种变化多端的颜色，迷惑我们的眼睛，妨碍我们的洞察力。 3. Such masses may also focally obstruct the biliary tract and lead to an elevated alkaline phosphatase. 肿物也可阻塞胆管，导致碱性磷酸酶升高。 4. But wherever Zhao went he would cause traffic jams and obstruct pavements as stunned crowds gathered to gawp. 但赵良所到之处，都会因惊讶的人们围观而造成塞车和道路阻塞。', '形容词: obstructive 副词: obstructively 名词: obstructer 过去式: obstructed 过去分词: obstructed 现在分词: obstructing 第三人称单数: obstructs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('threat', '[θret]', 'n.威胁；恐吓；凶兆', '1. His presence is a threat to our success. 他的出现对我们的成功是一个威胁。 2. The threat of an economic depression hangs over the world. 经济衰退的威胁笼罩着世界。 3. Pollution poses a threat to the continued existence of this species. 污染对这一物种的继续生存造成了威胁。 4. He took not notice of his father\'s threat. 他不理会他父亲的恐吓。', '过去式: threated 过去分词: threated 现在分词: threating 第三人称单数: threats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plentiful', '[\'plentɪfl]', 'adj.丰富的；多的；充裕的', '1. This place has plentiful material resources. 这地方的物质资源是丰富的。 2. Cellulosic biomass feedstock is inexpensive and plentiful. 纤维素生物量的供料是廉价和丰富的。 3. While full-time jobs may not be plentiful, project work is common. 虽然可能没那么多的全职工作，但项目工作是常见的。 4. Fish are abundant and plentiful in the lake behind my house. 我们家后面的湖中有非常多的鱼。', '副词: plentifully 名词: plentifulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loudspeaker', '[ˌlaʊd\'spiːkər]', 'n.扬声器；喇叭', '1. The nurse paged the doctor on the loudspeaker. 护士通过广播喊叫那位医生。 2. We heard the news over the loudspeaker. 我们听见扩音器里广播了这一消息。 3. The police addressed the crowd through a loudspeaker on their car. 警察通过他们汽车上的喇叭向人群喊话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('couch', '[kaʊtʃ]', 'n.长椅；睡椅；长沙发；兽穴 vt.表达；躺下 vi.埋伏；躺下', '1. Dad is sleeping on the couch. 爸爸在长椅上睡觉。 2. Little Tom was lolling about on the couch, eating sweets. 小汤姆懒洋洋地躺在睡椅上，吃着糖果。 3. His black leather couch looks expensive. 他的黑色皮沙发看上去很昂贵。 4. The rabbit sprang from its grassy couch. 兔子从草丛中跳出。 5. Poets couch their ideas in beautiful language. 诗人用美丽的语言传达他们的意念。', '名词: coucher 过去式: couched 过去分词: couched 现在分词: couching 第三人称单数: couches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bold', '[boʊld]', 'adj.大胆的；陡峭的；醒目的；粗体的；无礼的', '1. Bold outlines and warm colors characterize his dominate style in painting. 他大胆的绘画和所有的暖色调表现了他独有的绘画特色。 2. She was a shy girl, but she put on a bold front and went to the party. 她是个害羞的女孩子,然而她却装出一副勇敢的样子去参加聚会。 3. The peaks stood out in bold relief against the azure sky. 在蓝天的映衬下,山峰的轮廓极为明显。 4. A bold black headline screamed out from the front page. 在头版上出现了一条令人触目惊心的粗黑体大字标题。', '副词: boldly 比较级: bolder 最高级: boldest 名词: boldness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remain', '[rɪ\'meɪn]', 'v.剩余；逗留；留下；依然；保持 n.剩余物；遗迹；残骸', '1. We must learn to conserve what remains. 我们必须学会保存那些剩余的资源。 2. I didn\'t remain long in the city. 我没在那个城市逗留很长时间。 3. Though the sore being healed, yet a scar may remain. 伤口虽然痊愈, 却可能留下伤疤。 4. The present international situation remains tense and turbulent. 当前的国际局势依然紧张动荡。 5. After maintenance the main remains and remainders are left on the domain. 维修之后，主要遗骸和剩余物留在了领地上。', '过去式: remained 过去分词: remained 现在分词: remaining 第三人称单数: remains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gold', '[ɡoʊld]', 'adj.金色的；金制的 n.金币；金黄色；金牌；金子', '1. This gold frame sets off your painting well. 这金色的框架把你的画衬托。 2. The gold watchband is thin but heavy. 这条金色的表带薄薄的，但是很重。 3. The Olympic winner received a gold medal as an award. 奥林匹克的优胜者获得一枚金质奖章作为奖赏。 4. She wore a gold ring on her finger. 她的手指上戴了只金戒指。 5. The monetary system of some countries used to be based on gold. 过去有些国家的货币制度是金本位制的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inevitable', '[ɪn\'evɪtəbl]', 'adj.不可避免的；必然(发生)的', '1. You\'ll have to bow to the inevitable. 你将不得不向不可避免的事态低头。 2. But most agree that change is inevitable. 但她们多数人同意改变是不可避免的。', '副词: inevitably 名词: inevitability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sob', '[sɑːb]', 'v.抽泣；呜咽 n.呜咽；哭泣', '1. Then the man began to sob and walked away. 那个人开始抽泣,然后走开了。 2. Some children often sob themselves to sleep. 有些孩子常哭泣着睡着了。 3. The hard sob of anger barred her voice. 愤怒所产生的痛苦呜咽阻滞着她的语音。 4. It was a long, grieving sound, like a sigh--almost like a sob. 这一声叫喊又悠长又凄楚，似是长叹，又似是呜咽。 5. She sobbed into her handkerchief. 她用手绢掩面啜泣。', '副词: sobbingly 过去式: sobbed 过去分词: sobbed 现在分词: sobbing 第三人称单数: sobs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chill', '[tʃɪl]', 'v.(使)变冷；(使)扫兴；[冶]冷淬 n.寒冷；扫兴；寒心；着凉 adj.冷淡的；寒冷的', '1. Come by the fire you must be chilled to the marrow! 到火旁边来吧－－你一定冻坏了。 2. The night air chilled his bones. 夜间的寒气使他感到冰冷彻骨。 3. The raw weather chilled our enthusiasm for a swim. 天气阴冷，我们游泳的兴致大减。 4. There was a chill in the air this morning. 今天早上有点冷冰冰的。 5. The host gave him a chill reception. 主人(对客人而言)对他的接待是冷淡的。', '副词: chillingly 名词: chillness 过去式: chilled 过去分词: chilled 现在分词: chilling 第三人称单数: chills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wave', '[weɪv]', 'n.波浪；波纹；波 v.挥动；飘动', '1. The boat was smashed by a huge wave. 小船被一个巨浪掀翻胃。 2. She has a natural wave in her hair. 她的头发自然卷曲。 3. A compression wave in decelerating flow steepens. 压缩波在减速流中变陡。 4. This wave of excess density is sound. 这种过剩密度的波就是声波。 5. Bill waved his hand to us and then drove away. 比尔向我们挥手告别后开车走了。', '名词: waver 过去式: waved 过去分词: waved 现在分词: waving 第三人称单数: waves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ore', '[ɔːr]', 'n.矿石；矿', '1. We will make an assay of the ore that he brought. 我们将对他带来的矿石做实验鉴定。 2. The ore is smelted in this large factory. 这个大型工厂里熔炼矿石。 3. This is an area rich in ore. 这里是个矿产丰富的地区。 4. But few of them had actually dug up any ore. 然而他们中只有少数几个确实挖了矿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mad', '[mæd]', 'adj.发疯的，发狂似的；狂热的；鲁莽的；着迷的；生气的；极度激动的', '1. She was almost mad with grief when her son died. 她的儿子死去时，她悲伤得几乎疯了。 2. They are mad about football. 他们对足球很狂热。 3. It was a mad idea to climb the mountain in this bad weather. 在这种坏天气去爬山真是愚蠢。 4. Both brothers are mad about tennis. 兄弟俩对网球都很入迷。', '形容词: maddish 比较级: madder 最高级: maddest 过去式: madded 过去分词: madded 现在分词: madding 第三人称单数: mads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('epoch', '[\'epək]', 'n. 时期； 时代； 新纪元； 划时代的大事； <地质>世', '1. Ice age refers to the latest glacial epoch. 冰河时期指的是最近的一个冰川时期。 2. The Revolution had many of these men, proportioned to the epoch. 革命时期有过许多那样的人，都和那时代相称。 3. Einstein\'s theory marked a new epoch in history. 爱因斯坦的理论标志著历史上一个新时代的开始。 4. The epoch of revolution creates great figures. 革命时代造就伟大的人物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('towel', '[\'taʊəl]', 'n.毛巾；手巾 v.用毛巾擦', '1. I dry my hands and face with the towel. 我用毛巾擦干了双手和面部。 2. She mops her tears with a towel. 她用毛巾擦眼泪。 3. We installed a stainless steel towel rail on the wall. 我们在墙上装了一个不锈钢的挂毛巾的横杆。 4. Sop up the water with a paper towel. 用纸巾把水吸乾。 5. He toweled himself dry. 他用毛巾擦干身体。', '过去式: toweled/towelled 过去分词: toweled/towelled 现在分词: toweling/towelling 第三人称单数: towels/towels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fruitful', '[\'fruːtfl]', 'adj.多产的；富有成效的', '1. He is really a fruitful novelist. 他真是一位多产的小说家。 2. Some adult male and female are occupied in sowing grain on the fertile fruitful soil. 一些成年男女正在肥沃多产的土地上忙碌地播种谷物。 3. This is perhaps the most fruitful new insight we have in the field of organization. 这也许是我们在组织领域中所获得最富有成效的新见识。 4. The uncommon man is merely the common man thinking and dreaming of success in larger terms and in more fruitful areas. 杰出人物只是从更广角度和更富有成效的领域思考和梦想成功的普通人。', '副词: fruitfully 名词: fruitfulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('best', '[best]', 'adj.最好的 adv.最；最好地 n.最好的人(或物) v.优于；打败', '1. The facilities were not ideal but we managed as best we could. 设备不理想，但我们已经尽了最大的努力。 2. He\'s difficult at the best of times usually he\'s impossible. 他即使在情绪最好的时候，都很难相处－－平常就更令人受不了了。 3. You had best not accept the offer. 你最好是不要接纳这要求。 4. Take whatsoever measures you consider best. 采取任何你认为最好的措施。 5. He would try to best his previous time. 他竭尽全力去打破自己以前的纪录。', '过去式: bested 过去分词: bested 现在分词: besting 第三人称单数: bests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('electrician', '[ɪˌlek\'trɪʃn]', 'n.电工；电气技师', '1. He\'s neither an electrician nor a mechanic. 他既不是电工也不是技工。 2. Don\'t meddle with the electrical wiring: you\'re not an electrician. 别瞎动电线线路，你又不是电工。 3. We need an electrician to mend the iron. 我们要请电工修理熨斗。 4. He\'s apprenticed to an electrician. 他去跟一名电工技师当学徒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('doubt', '[daʊt]', 'n.怀疑；疑惑；悬而未定 vt.怀疑；不信任 vi.不确定', '1. There is no doubt that we will be successful. 毫无疑问我们会成功的。 2. Although a very religious man, he is still troubled by occasional doubts. 他虽然笃信宗教，但有时仍感到迷惘。 3. The outcome of this discussion is still in doubt. 这次讨论的结果还未定。 4. She\'s been feeling ill these days, so I doubt that she\'ll feel up to going to the country this weekend. 她最近一直都不舒服,所以我怀疑周末她是否能到乡下去。 5. She said that I was getting into the habit of doubting. 她说我渐渐地好像对什么都不确定。', '名词: doubter 过去式: doubted 过去分词: doubted 现在分词: doubting 第三人称单数: doubts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blunder', '[\'blʌndər]', 'n.大错 v.失策；绊倒；弄糟', '1. He made a blunder in front of his girlfriend. 他在女朋友面前犯了大错。 2. I saw that I had been guilty of a careless blunder. 我意识到自己因疏忽而酿成大错。 3. I made a terrible blunder in introducing her to my husband. 我把她介绍给我的丈夫是犯了一个极大的错误。 4. I hope you will not blunder again . 我希望你不要再犯大错。', '副词: blunderingly 名词: blunderer 过去式: blundered 过去分词: blundered 现在分词: blundering 第三人称单数: blunders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('born', '[bɔːrn]', 'adj.出生的；与生俱来的 动词bear的过去分词.', '1. The youngest is a born rider of the rails. 小儿子是天生的流浪儿。 2. Meg was born into a large family. 梅格出生在一个大家庭。 3. I\'ve never heard such nonsense in all my born days! 我一生中从未听到过这种胡言乱语。 4. Natalie was born to be a dancer. 娜塔莉天生就是一个舞者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('distinct', '[dɪ\'stɪŋkt]', 'adj.明显的；清晰的；不同的；独特的', '1. There is a distinct possibility that she\'ll be your teacher next term. 她下学期当你们的老师的可能性非常大。 2. On the contrary, he was looking at Harry with distinct pride. 相反,他望着哈利的目光中带着明显的自豪。 3. There\'s a distinct smell of cigarettes every time he comes into the room. 他每次进房间,都带着一股浓重的烟味。 4. Two people may both dream of the other,and find that their dreams had a distinct connection. 两个人可能互相梦见对方,而且发现他们的梦有着清晰的联系。', '副词: distinctly 名词: distinctness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flaw', '[flɔː]', 'n.瑕疵；缺陷；破绽；裂缝 v.使破裂；有瑕疵', '1. Unfortunately, I found that your work had a tiny flaw. 很不幸 2. The flaw in this vase makes it less valuable. 这个花瓶因为有点缺陷，不那么值钱了。 3. I can\'t find a flaw in his argument. 在他的论点中,我找不到任何破绽。 4. Your argument has a fatal flaw. 你的论点有一个致命的错误。 5. The jealous colleague decided to flaw the project plans. 这名嫉妒的同事决定给这些项目计划搞破坏。', '形容词: flawy 过去式: flawed 过去分词: flawed 现在分词: flawing 第三人称单数: flaws');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('excellent', '[\'eksələnt]', 'adj.杰出的；优秀的；极好的', '1. She would have made an excellent teacher. 她本可以成为杰出的教师。 2. As soon as she learns the office routine, she will be an excellent assistant. 她一旦熟悉了办公室的日常事务,就会成为一名优秀的助手。 3. Hawaii is an excellent tourist resort. 夏威夷是极好的旅游胜地。 4. He worked out an excellent idea. 他想出了一个极好的主意。', '副词: excellently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('long', '[lɔːŋ]', 'adj.长的；冗长的；久的；长音的 adv.长期地；久地；用于名词后强调某事发生在某整段时间 v.渴望 n.长时间；长音节；囤积商品者', '1. She was slender and had long dark hair. 她身材苗条，有一头长长的黑发。 2. She bought some roses with long stems. 她买了一些枝干很长的玫瑰花。 3. He delivered a long prose full of platitudes. 他发表了一篇充满陈词滥调的文章。 4. I haven\'t seen him for a long while. 我已经很久没见到他了。 5. I haven\'t known her long. 我认识她不久。 6. She longed to be back in China. 她渴望回到中国。 7. This won\'t take long. 这要不了多久。', '比较级: longer 最高级: longest 过去式: longed 过去分词: longed 现在分词: longing 第三人称单数: longs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('swamp', '[swɑːmp]', 'n.沼泽；湿地；困境 v.淹没；使陷于困境；使忙于应付', '1. In the swamp we were beset by mosquitoes. 我们在沼泽地受到蚊子的围攻。 2. The heavy rain has turned the small garden into a swamp. 大雨使这小花园变成了一块沼泽地。 3. Walk through the swamp and we can see the hunter\'s cabin. 走过这片湿地就能看到猎人的小屋了。 4. Their company is in a financial swamp. 他们的公司陷入了财政困境。 5. In summer visitors swamp the island. 夏天，这个岛上熙熙攘攘，人满为患。', '形容词: swampy 名词: swampiness 过去式: swamped 过去分词: swamped 现在分词: swamping 第三人称单数: swamps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pen', '[pen]', 'n.钢笔；笔；写作；围栏；雌天鹅 v.写；把…关在圈中', '1. The pen slips out of my fingers. 钢笔从我指缝中滑下去了。 2. Put down my pen and stop fiddling! 把我的钢笔放下，别用手玩弄！ 3. He dipped his pen in the ink. 他拿钢笔蘸墨水。 4. She fumbled about in her handbag for a pen. 她在手提袋中搜寻钢笔。 5. She penned a few words of thanks. 她写了几句致谢的话。', '名词: penner 过去式: penned 过去分词: penned 现在分词: penning 第三人称单数: pens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('May', '[meɪ]', 'aux.可以，能够；可能，也许；祝，愿；会，能 n.[大写] 五月', '1. Well, and who may you be? 那麽，你是谁呢? 2. That might be our taxi. 那辆有可能是我们的计程车。 3. That may be our taxi now! 那辆可能就是我们的计程车了。 4. Might I suggest another time? 我可以建议另找个时间吗？', '过去式: might');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('perspective', '[pər\'spektɪv]', 'n.远景；看法；透视 adj.透视的', '1. A fine perspective opened out before us. 一幅美丽的远景展开在我们眼前。 2. Do you agree with this perspective? 你同意这个看法吗? 3. The painting provides us with one of the earliest examples of the use of perspective. 那幅画给我们提供了采用透视画法的最早的范例。 4. The first row of each perspective shows its name. 每个透视的第一行都显示该透视的名称。', '形容词: perspectival 副词: perspectively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ninety', '[\'naɪnti]', 'num.九十', '1. He was born in the nineties of the nineteen century. 他生于十九世纪九十年代。 2. He must be going on for ninety. 他准有九十岁了。', '名词复数: nineties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('authority', '[ə\'θɔːrəti]', 'n.权力；官方；当局；职权；权威', '1. The government is the highest authority in the country. 政府是国家的最高权力机构。 2. Authorities say the fires do look suspicious. 官方表示，火灾看起来确实很奇怪。 3. Both the authorities and the media wondered whether insider dealing had been going on. 官方跟媒体都在怀疑这里面是不是存在内幕交易。 4. The authorities did not interfere with us. 当局不干涉我们。', '名词复数: authorities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('humorous', '[\'hjuːmərəs]', 'adj.幽默的；诙谐的', '1. I have plenty of humorous tales. 我有许多幽默的故事。 2. Indeed he has a solemn face, but he is very humorous at heart. 他的确有一副严肃的脸孔，但内心却是很富幽默感。 3. She writes humorous songs when she is in the right vein. 她在心情不好的时候写诙谐的歌曲。 4. It tells a romantic and humorous love. 它讲述了一个浪漫而诙谐的爱情故事。', '副词: humorously 名词: humorousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cruel', '[\'kruːəl]', 'adj.残酷的；残忍的；引起痛苦的', '1. The feudal barons were cruel to the people. 封建贵族对人民很残酷。 2. That emperor was a cruel despot. 那个皇帝是个残酷的专制君主。 3. The death of their daughter was a cruel blow. 女儿的死对他们是一个残酷的打击。 4. He is a cruel assassin. 他是个残忍的杀手。', '副词: cruelly 比较级: crueler/crueller 最高级: cruelest/cruellest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('declare', '[dɪ\'kler]', 'v.宣布（声明）；申报；声明', '1. I now declare this meeting open. 我现在宣布会议开幕。 2. Britain declared war on Germany in 1914. 英国在1914年向德国宣战。 3. The customs asked me if I had anything to declare. 海关人员问我是否有要报税的东西。 4. Do you have anything to declare, jewelry or cash? 你有没有什么东西要申报?珠宝或现金?', '形容词: declarable 名词: declarer 过去式: declared 过去分词: declared 现在分词: declaring 第三人称单数: declares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('celebrate', '[\'selɪbreɪt]', 'v.庆祝；庆贺；颂扬', '1. Let\'s celebrate! 让我们好好庆祝一下吧！ 2. People in the city held a great party to celebrate their victory. 本市的市民举行了盛大的晚会庆祝他们的胜利。 3. They had a family feast to celebrate it. 他们举办家宴以示庆贺。 4. He read us a sonnet that celebrates love. 他给我们读了一首歌颂爱情的十四行诗。', '形容词: celebratory 名词: celebration 过去式: celebrated 过去分词: celebrated 现在分词: celebrating 第三人称单数: celebrates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('agreeable', '[ə\'ɡriːəbl]', 'adj.愉快的；和蔼可亲的；欣然同意的；一致的', '1. I enjoyed an agreeable holiday this summer. 今年夏天我度过了一个愉快的假期。 2. We spent a most agreeable day together. 我们在一起度过了非常愉快的一天。 3. I find her a very agreeable woman. 我发现她是个和蔼可亲的女人。 4. To a more agreeable adviser, or one from whom he would be more likely to learn, Mr. Harthouse could never be recommended. 赫德豪士先生表示谁也不能给他介绍一位更和蔼可亲的顾问，或者他会更可能向之学习的顾问了。', '副词: agreeably 名词: agreeability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('speak', '[spiːk]', 'v.讲；说话；演说；发言', '1. Does anyone speak English here? 这儿有人会说英语吗？ 2. I\'m quite capable of speaking for myself, thank you! 我还是有能力把话说清楚的，谢谢你吧。 3. The patient is too weak to speak. 病人太衰弱了，不能说话。 4. He will speak on the air this evening. 今晚他将在广播中演说。', '形容词: speakable 过去式: spoke 过去分词: spoken 现在分词: speaking 第三人称单数: speaks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('international', '[ˌɪntər\'næʃnəl]', 'adj.国际的；世界性的 n.国际比赛', '1. I think international calls are very expensive. 我认为国际电话费用很高。 2. The country violated the international agreement. 这个国家违反了国际协议。 3. The drug problem is international. 毒品问题是世界性的。 4. He watched the France-Scotland Rugby international. 他观看了法国对苏格兰的橄榄球赛。', '副词: internationally 名词: internationality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peace', '[piːs]', 'n.和平；安静', '1. The situation poses a grave threat to world peace. 这局势对世界和平构成了严重的威胁。 2. The dove is the emblem of peace. 鸽子是和平的象徵。 3. There is an atmosphere of peace and calm in the country. 在乡间有一种和平宁静的气氛。 4. She\'s never at peace with herself. 她总是静不下来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forth', '[fɔːrθ]', 'adv.向前；向外；露出', '1. The guard walked back and forth in front of the gate. 警卫在大门前走来走去。 2. He went forth into the desert to pray 他向前走到沙漠中祈祷。 3. Suddenly oil sprang forth from the pipe. 油突然从管子里喷了出来。 4. The trees burst forth in spring. 树木在春天开始抽芽。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Sunday', '[\'sʌndeɪ]', 'n.星期日 adj.星期日的', '1. Sunday is the first day of the week. 星期日是一周的第一天。 2. I bought a new fishing rod last Sunday. 上星期日我新买了一个鱼竿。 3. We\'re sold out of Sunday papers, sir. 先生，星期日的报纸我们全卖光了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('financial', '[faɪ\'nænʃl]', 'adj.金融的；财政的；<非正式>有钱的', '1. He is an adventurer in financial field. 他是金融领域的投机者。 2. And I got the financial support after two years. 两年后我终于取得了奖学金。 3. I hear you are in poor financial straits. 我听说你处于经济困难之中。 4. This company was in serious financial difficulties. 这家公司陷入严重的财政困难。', '副词: financially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reliable', '[rɪ\'laɪəbl]', 'adj.可靠的；可信的', '1. I don\'t think he is a reliable man. 我认为他不是一个可靠的人。 2. She may be slow but at least she\'s reliable. 她迟钝是迟钝，但无论如何她很可靠。 3. A reliable car is worth its weight in gold. 靠得住的汽车就是无价之宝。 4. A man who is dead to the justice is not reliable. 一个没有正义感的人是不可信的。', '副词: reliably 名词: reliability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('switch', '[swɪtʃ]', 'n.转换；开关；鞭子 v.改变；交换；转换；鞭打', '1. How do I switch to the next major release branch? 如何转换为下个主要发布版本分支？ 2. The current will switch over after I push this button. 我按下这个按钮之后，电流会被转换。 3. I wish to turn on the light, where is the switch? 我想要开亮那一支电灯,请问开关在哪儿? 4. The father whipped his child with a switch. 父亲用鞭子抽打他的孩子。 5. No, hold it a second, switch that to roast chicken. 不，等一等，把那个换成烤子鸡。', '形容词: switchable 名词: switcher 过去式: switched 过去分词: switched 现在分词: switching 第三人称单数: switches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drain', '[dreɪn]', 'v.排出；排干；喝光；耗尽 n.下水道；消耗', '1. We must dig a trench to drain away the water. 我们必须挖一条沟排水。 2. They drain the swamp and turn it into fertile land. 他们排干沼泽地的水,将它变成了肥沃的土地。 3. They all rose and drained their glasses. 他们都站了起来,一饮而尽。 4. She felt drained of energy. 她感到精疲力竭。 5. We have to call a plumber to unblock the drain. 我们得叫管工来通一通下水道。', '形容词: drainable 名词: drainer 过去式: drained 过去分词: drained 现在分词: draining 第三人称单数: drains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exterior', '[ɪk\'stɪriər]', 'n.外部；外表；外景 adj.外部的；表面的；对外的；户外的', '1. Advertising normally produces a design for the exterior of the container. 广告部一般是作包装的外部设计。 2. The exterior of the building is very unattractive. 这建筑物的外观很不起眼。 3. He is a gentle man with a rough exterior. 他是一个外表粗鲁但性情温和的男人。 4. She maintained a calm exterior, though really she was furious. 在外表上她保持着平静，但实际上她生气极了。 5. We are painting the exterior wall of the house. 我们正在给房子的外墙涂漆。', '副词: exteriorly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('broom', '[bruːm]', 'n.扫帚；金雀花 vt.清扫', '1. We use broom to sweep the floor. 我们用扫帚扫地。 2. He picked up the broom to help me sweep the floor. 他拿起扫帚帮我扫地。 3. He stopped sweeping and rested on the broom. 他停止扫地，倚着扫帚休息。 4. The broom blooms when the bluebells bloom. 野风信子开花时金雀花也开花了。 5. He always had to broom the floor. 他总是不得不打扫地板。', '形容词: broomy 过去式: broomed 过去分词: broomed 现在分词: brooming 第三人称单数: brooms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cap', '[kæp]', 'n.帽子；盖子；顶；上限 vt.超过；加盖于；戴帽；覆盖；完成；设限 vi.脱帽致意', '1. He took off his cap. 他摘掉帽子。 2. It\'s better to put the cap back on the bottle. 最好把瓶盖盖上。 3. The government should impose an cap across the gas price. 政府应当给燃气价格强制规定上限。 4. That\'s a good joke but I think I can cap it. 那是个好笑话，但是我可以说得更好。 5. They cap when they pass the president. 他们经过院长面前时脱帽行礼。', '过去式: capped 过去分词: capped 现在分词: capping 第三人称单数: caps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jar', '[dʒɑːr]', 'n.广口瓶；坛子；刺耳声；震动 vi.发刺耳声；不协调；震荡；冲突 vt.扰乱；震动', '1. I can\'t get the lid off this jar. 我打不开这广口瓶的盖子。 2. The jar contains ten glasses of water. 这只大口瓶能装十杯水。 3. I need a jar to make the krauts. 我需要一个坛子做泡菜。 4. He fashioned the clay into a jar. 他用粘土做成一个陶土罐子。 5. The iron gate jarred when he opened it. 他开门时，铁门发出刺耳的嘎嘎声。 6. The children\'s screams jar my nerves. 孩子们的尖叫声使我神经不安。', '副词: jarringly 名词: jarful 过去式: jarred 过去分词: jarred 现在分词: jarring 第三人称单数: jars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sentence', '[\'sentəns]', 'n.句子；判决 vt.宣判；判决', '1. It is a fact that I have written this sentence. 我写了这个句子是事实。 2. The judge will pass sentence tomorrow after looking at the report. 法官看完报告后明天会做出判决。 3. He has been sentenced to pay a fine of 1000 pounds. 他被判罚款1000英镑。 4. He was sentenced to death. 他被处以死刑。', '形容词: sentential 副词: sententially 过去式: sentenced 过去分词: sentenced 现在分词: sentencing 第三人称单数: sentences');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('organic', '[ɔːr\'ɡænɪk]', 'adj.器官的；有机的；有组织的；根本的；接近自然的 n.有机物质', '1. The illness is organic in origin. 该病起初是器质性疾患。 2. I am not good at organic chemistry. 我的有机化学学得不好。 3. You can apply heat to decompose organic compounds. 你可以加热来分解有机化合物。 4. The music is organic to the story. 这首乐曲是这个故事必不可少的组成部分。 5. Oil-yielding organic matter is contained in the shales. 在这些页岩里有产油的有机物质。', '副词: organically 名词: organicity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('corresponding', '[ˌkɔːrə\'spɑːndɪŋ]', 'adj.相当的；相应的；一致的 动词correspond的现在分词形式.', '1. You will be punished in a way corresponding to your profession. 你们将受到相当于你的职业的处罚。 2. Sales are up 10% on the corresponding period last year. 销售额和去年同时期相比增加了10%25。 3. Investment in the subway will bring a corresponding improvement in services. 对地铁进行投资将使服务得到相应的提升。 4. The corresponding results have a good agreement with the reactor dynamics. 得到了与相应反应堆动力学很一致的结果。', '副词: correspondingly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bait', '[beɪt]', 'n.饵；引诱 v.以饵引诱；逗弄；中途休息', '1. The fish snapped at the bait. 那鱼一下子咬住了鱼饵。 2. Earth worms are often used as bait. 蚯蚓常用作鱼饵。 3. The steaming cake was a bait for the hungry boy. 那热气腾腾的蛋糕对这个饥饿的男孩是个诱惑。 4. As soon as I mentioned money he rose to the bait, and became really interested. 我一提钱他便怦然心动，上了我的钩。 5. They bait the mousetrap with stale cheese. 他们用变质的乳酪作捕鼠夹的诱饵。', '名词: baiter 过去式: baited 过去分词: baited 现在分词: baiting 第三人称单数: baits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scream', '[skriːm]', 'n.尖叫声 v.尖叫；（指风﹑ 机器等）发出大而尖的声音', '1. The patient gave out a scream of pain. 病人痛苦地尖叫一声。 2. A scream broke the silence of the night. 一声尖叫划破了寂静的夜空。 3. The boy was screaming with pain. 这男孩痛得尖叫起来。 4. People scream in fright,in anger,and in sudden pain. 人们在害怕、生气或痛苦时会尖叫。', '副词: screamingly 过去式: screamed 过去分词: screamed 现在分词: screaming 第三人称单数: screams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('metre', '[\'miːtər]', 'n.米；公尺；计量器 n.（诗的）韵律；格律 =meter(美).', '1. This cloth is sold by the metre. 这种布按米出售。 2. He cuts off a metre of cloth from the roll. 他从那卷布上剪下一米。 3. O\'Brien moved the cage nearer.It was less than a metre from Winston\'s face. 奥勃良把铁笼子移得更近一些，距离温斯顿的眼前不到一公尺了。 4. It was sealed by a wall and contained chalky soil to the depth of one metre. 它被一堵墙密封着,仿如白垩时期的泥土深达一公尺。 5. Many modernists think that rhyme and metre hamper the poet\'s free expression. 很多现代派人认为韵律妨碍了诗人的自由发挥。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('regulate', '[\'reɡjuleɪt]', 'vt.调整；校准；管理；控制', '1. Specification could be regulated as buyer\'s request. 指标可根据客户要求进行调整。 2. Regretfully, we can\'t regulate the irregular liner on the gulf. 遗憾的是我们不能调整海湾上不定期的班船。 3. Your watch is always slow; it needs to be regulated. 你的手表总是慢，需要校准一下。 4. Accidents sometimes happen even in the best regulated families. 即便是在管理最好的家庭，事故有时也会发生的。', '形容词: regulative 过去式: regulated 过去分词: regulated 现在分词: regulating 第三人称单数: regulates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peanut', '[\'piːnʌt]', 'n.花生；<俚>渺小的人或物', '1. He likes to eat peanut jam. 他喜欢吃花生酱。 2. The peanut develops below the ground. 花生在地下结果。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rabbit', '[\'ræbɪt]', 'n.兔子', '1. The rabbit burrowed under the fence. 兔子在篱笆下打洞。 2. The magician conjured a rabbit out of his hat. 魔术师从他的帽子里变出一只兔子。 3. She is as timorous as a rabbit. 她胆小得像只兔子。 4. The eagle dived down on the rabbit. 那只鹰向兔子猛扑下来。', '名词: rabbiter 名词复数: rabbits 过去式: rabbited 过去分词: rabbited 现在分词: rabbiting 第三人称单数: rabbits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fright', '[fraɪt]', 'n.惊骇；惊恐；<口>怪人', '1. Hearing the news, we turned pale with fright. 听到这消息后，我们惊骇失色。 2. Tom\'s fright weakened every muscle in his body. 汤姆所受的惊骇使他全身的肌肉都没有劲了。 3. He cried out in fright as the dark figure approached. 那个黑影向他逼近，他吓得叫了出来。 4. He gave me a fright by bursting into a sudden laughter. 他突然大笑起来，吓了我一跳。', '过去式: frighted 过去分词: frighted 现在分词: frighting 第三人称单数: frights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inside', '[ˌɪn\'saɪd]', 'adj.里面的 adv.在里面 n.内部 prep.在 ... 里面', '1. All the inside rooms were skylighted. 所有里面的房间都装了天窗。 2. Maybe it is in your inside pocket. 它可能在你衣服里面的口袋里。 3. She shook it to make certain there was nothing inside. 她把它摇了摇，想知道里面确实没有东西。 4. We have to play inside because it is raining. 因为天下雨，我们不得不在屋里玩。 5. The driver behind me tried to overtake on the inside. 我后面的驾驶员想从内车道超过我。 6. He parked his car inside the gate. 他把车停在大门里面。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('depict', '[dɪ\'pɪkt]', 'vt.描述；描绘；画', '1. Her novel depicts life in modern London. 她的小说描写的是伦敦现代的生活。 2. The book depicts him as a rather unpleasant character. 这本书把他刻画成一个相当令人讨厌的人物。 3. This painting depicts the birth of Venus. 这幅画描绘的是维纳斯的诞生。 4. It\'s a picture depicting him as a clown. 这是一幅把他画成小丑的画。', '名词: depiction 过去式: depicted 过去分词: depicted 现在分词: depicting 第三人称单数: depicts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nor', '[nɔːr]', 'conj.也不；也没有 adv.也不；也没有 abbr.诺曼人(=Norman) abbr.北方（=North） abbr.挪威（= Norway） abbr.挪威人（=Norwegian）', '1. It is neither hot nor cold in winter here. 这里冬天既不热也不冷。 2. He\'s neither an electrician nor a mechanic. 他既不是电工也不是技工。 3. Neither he nor I have free time. 他没有闲功夫，我也没有闲功夫。 4. We neither moved nor made any noise. 我们没有动也没有出声。 5. It is neither hot nor cold in winter here. 这里冬天既不热也不冷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('romantic', '[roʊ\'mæntɪk]', 'adj.浪漫的；不切实际的 n.浪漫的人', '1. I was told that Spain is a romantic nation. 有人告诉我说，西班牙是个浪漫的国家。 2. It is said that Frenchmen are among the most romantic people in the world. 据说法国人是世界上最浪漫的民族之一。 3. His head is stuffed with silly romantic ideas. 他满脑子天真的想法。 4. She has romantic notions about becoming a famous actress. 她心里充满幻想，总希望有一天会成为著名演员。 5. Romantic is the last thing I am. 我是最不浪漫的人。', '副词: romantically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('carbon', '[\'kɑːrbən]', 'n.碳；复写纸；复本；碳精棒', '1. Carbon dioxide consists of carbon and oxygen. 二氧化碳是由碳和氧组成的。 2. He decided to use carbon because it does not melt. 于是，他决定用碳，因为碳不易熔化。 3. I make a carbon copy of my documents. 我用复写纸复写文件。 4. She put the carbon paper in the wrong way round. 他把复写纸放反了。', '形容词: carbonous');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resign', '[rɪ\'zaɪn]', 'v.辞职；放弃；顺从；听任', '1. Have you heard of her intention to resign? 你听到她打算辞职的传闻了吗？ 2. He decided to resign his claim to the copyright. 他决定放弃对版权的要求。 3. He has resigned himself to the fact that he will lose the job. 他已经接受他将要失去这份工作的现实。 4. The team refused to resign themselves to being defeated. 该队不甘失败。', '名词: resigner 过去式: resigned 过去分词: resigned 现在分词: resigning 第三人称单数: resigns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('naughty', '[\'nɔːti]', 'adj.顽皮的；淘气的；不妥的', '1. His dog scared that naughty boy away. 他的狗把那个顽皮的孩子吓走了。 2. You naughty boy! I\'ve told you not to play in the street. 你这顽皮孩子！我说过，叫你别在马路上玩。 3. This naughty boy is really troublesome. 这个淘气的男孩子真是惹人烦。 4. The naughty boy hid the books in the shrub. 这个淘气的孩子把书藏在了灌木丛里。', '副词: naughtily 比较级: naughtier 最高级: naughtiest 名词: naughtiness 名词复数: naughties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('artistic', '[ɑːr\'tɪstɪk]', 'adj.艺术的', '1. She has artistic tendencies. 她有艺术气质。 2. We are disciples of the artistic leader. 我们是那位艺术领袖的追随者。 3. He is a man with an artistic temperament. 他是个有艺术家气质的男子。 4. Our artistic director was instrumental in persuading the orchestra to come. 我们的艺术指导帮助请来管弦乐队。', '副词: artistically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fasten', '[\'fæsn]', 'vt.拴紧；使固定；系；强加于 vi.固定；系紧；抓紧', '1. Do not fasten all the windows up while you sleep. 睡觉时不要将所有的窗户都关紧。 2. For your own safety,please fasten your seat belts. 安全起见，请系紧安全带。 3. I fastened the pages together with a paperclip. 我用一个纸夹把那几页纸夹在一起。 4. The little boy has learnt to fasten shoelaces. 这小男孩已学会系鞋带了。 5. What can I use to fasten on this clip? 我用什么才能将这个夹子固定好?', '名词: fastener 过去式: fastened 过去分词: fastened 现在分词: fastening 第三人称单数: fastens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('carry', '[\'kæri]', 'v.携带；运送；搬运；带有；传播；承载 n.【计】进位；运载', '1. She came in carrying an important-looking piece of paper. 她进来时,拿着一份看来很重要的文件。 2. This is a dangerous area, so don\'t carry too much cash on you. 这个地区很危险，所以你身上不要带太多现金。 3. Pipes carry oil across the desert to the east. 输油管把石油经过沙漠运送到东部。 4. The box is so heavy that I can\'t carry it. 箱子太重了,我搬不动。', '名词复数: carries 过去式: carried 过去分词: carried 现在分词: carrying 第三人称单数: carries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('keen', '[kiːn]', 'adj.敏锐的；强烈的；锋利的；热衷的；精明的', '1. The blind have a keen sense of touch. 盲人有敏锐的触觉。 2. Their keen eyes can penetrate the water to a depth of forty feet. 他们锐利的眼睛能透过水面看到40 英尺的深处。 3. Be brave, a fence between makes love more keen. 勇敢点,受到阻隔的爱情会更强烈。 4. The razor has a very keen edge. 这把剃刀有锋利的口。', '副词: keenly 比较级: keener 最高级: keenest 名词: keenness 过去式: keened 过去分词: keened 现在分词: keening 第三人称单数: keens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('square', '[skwer]', 'n.正方形；广场；街区；平方；直角尺；<俚>古板的人 adj.正方形的；规矩的；结实的；公正的；断然的 v.一致；结清；收买；使 ... 成方形；使成平方；调整 adv.成直角；直接的；正方形地', '1. The little girl drew a square on the paper. 小女孩在纸上画了一个正方形。 2. Everybody goes to this vast square in the evening. 每天傍晚，人人都上这宽阔的广场上来。 3. The crowds in the square were elated by the news. 这消息使广场上的人群欢欣鼓舞。 4. 25 is a perfect square of 5. 25是5的完全平方。 5. A handkerchief is usually square. 手帕通常是正方形的。 6. His conduct does not square with his words. 他言行不一致。 7. The road turned square to the left. 这条路成直角向左转去。', '副词: squarely 比较级: squarer 最高级: squarest 名词: squareness 过去式: squared 过去分词: squared 现在分词: squaring 第三人称单数: squares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('controversial', '[ˌkɑːntrə\'vɜːrʃl]', 'adj.有争议的；引起争论的', '1. We tried to stay away from controversial topics at the dinner party. 晚宴上我们尽力避免一些有争议的话题。 2. This is a controversial question. 这是个引起争论的问题。', '副词: controversially 名词: controversialist');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invention', '[ɪn\'venʃn]', 'n.发明；虚构；发明物', '1. The invention of the computer marked the beginning of a new era. 计算机的发明标志着一个新时代的开始。 2. Necessity is the mother of invention. 需要是发明之母。 3. This story is apparently a complete invention. 这个故事显然完全是虚构的。 4. The whole thing is an invention of a newspaper. 整件事都是一家报纸虚构的。', '形容词: inventional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drama', '[\'drɑːmə]', 'n.戏剧；剧本；戏剧艺术；戏剧性事件', '1. I have no interest in drama. 我对戏剧不感兴趣。 2. The Elizabethan period was the golden age of English drama. 伊丽莎白时期是英国戏剧的黄金时代。 3. He has written a historical drama. 他已写了一个历史剧本。 4. The school encourages free expression in art, drama and creative writing. 学校鼓励师生在艺术、 戏剧和文学创作上自由发挥。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quarterly', '[\'kwɔːrtərli]', 'adj.季度的 adv.每季一次 n.季刊', '1. The quarterly dividend is their cardinal goal, and quick fixes are the means to accomplish it. 每个季度的分红是他们的主要目标，只要能最快地实现这个目标任何手段都成。 2. Lead the quarterly budgeting process and the monthly cash flow reporting and forecasting. 领导编制每一季度的预算以及定期的资金报告和预测。 3. This journal is bimonthly, and that one quarterly. 这本杂志是双月刊，那本是季刊。 4. Research Quarterly for Exercise and Sport. 锻炼和运动研究季刊。', '名词复数: quarterlies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fear', '[fɪr]', 'n.担心；害怕；恐惧；【中药学】相畏 v.害怕；担心；恐惧', '1. He is haunted by the fear that the police will find the truth. 他坐立难安,担心警察最终会发现真相。 2. The thought of returning filled him with fear. 一想到还要回去,他心里就害怕。 3. Crusoe stared at the footprint, full of fear. 克鲁索盯着脚印,心里充满了恐惧。 4. The refugees fear persecution if they return to their own country. 难民们害怕回到自己的国家后会惨遭迫害。', '名词: fearer 过去式: feared 过去分词: feared 现在分词: fearing 第三人称单数: fears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('qualify', '[\'kwɑːlɪfaɪ]', 'vt.使具备资格；描述；[语]修饰 vi.取得资格；合格', '1. This test will qualify you to fly an aircraft. 这次考试将使你取得驾驶飞机的资格。 2. His knowledge and skills qualify him for the job. 他的知识和技能使他有资格担任这项工作。 3. Your passport qualifies you to receive free medical treatment. 你所持的护照可使你享有免费医疗。 4. I qualify it as a plot. 我说它是一个阴谋。 5. I won\'t qualify until next year. 我明年才具备资格。', '过去式: qualified 过去分词: qualified 现在分词: qualifying 第三人称单数: qualifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unanimous', '[ju\'nænɪməs]', 'adj.全体一致的；一致同意的', '1. The Chinese are unanimous in their condemnation. 全中国人民一致提出谴责。 2. Politicians from all parties were completely unanimous in condemning his action. 所有党派的政治家们都一致谴责他的行为。 3. He was elected with unanimous approval. 他以全体一致同意而中选。 4. The committee were unanimous that the application should be turned down. 委员会一致同意拒绝这项申请。', '副词: unanimously 名词: unanimousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('faulty', '[\'fɔːlti]', 'adj.有缺陷的；不合格的；有错误的；有缺点的', '1. This store warrants the return of any faulty goods. 这家店包退所有有缺陷的货物。 2. I got an electric shock from that faulty light switch. 那个有毛病的电灯开关把我电了一下。 3. Send these faulty goods back to the manufacturer. 把这些次货退还给厂家。 4. Consumers are encouraged to complain about faulty goods. 要鼓励消费者对劣质商品投诉。', '副词: faultily 比较级: faultier 最高级: faultiest 名词: faultiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suffice', '[sə\'faɪs]', 'vi.足够；使满足 vt.使 ... 足够', '1. The rations will suffice until next week. 这些口粮足够吃到下星期。 2. An hour should suffice for the journey. 这点路程一小时足够了。 3. The rules will suffice for all ordinary needs. 这些规定将能满足所有一般场合的需要。 4. Two meals a day suffice an old man. 老人一天二餐就足够了。', '名词: sufficer 过去式: sufficed 过去分词: sufficed 现在分词: sufficing 第三人称单数: suffices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flu', '[fluː]', 'n.流行性感冒', '1. I got flu and was out of commission for a week. 我得了流感，一星期没工作。 2. The school was closed because of the flu. 因为流行性感冒全校停止上课。 3. I caught a flu and had to lie in the bed. 我得了流感，不得不卧床休息。 4. His flu infected his wife. 他把流行性感冒传染给妻子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seaside', '[\'siːsaɪd]', 'n.海边 adj.海边(的)；海滨(的)', '1. He is walking down the seaside. 他正沿海边走去。 2. We had an outing to the seaside last summer. 我们去年夏天去海边旅行。 3. The seaside fish market is a ready food supply for scavenging seabirds. 海边鱼市是觅食海鸟现成的食物供应地。 4. The seaside city is subject to frequent typhoon. 这座海滨城市经常遭受台风的袭击。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('labor', '[\'leɪbər]', 'n.工人；劳工；工作；分娩；劳力 v.苦干；劳动；致力于；过分详尽阐述 adj.劳工的；劳动的', '1. The country is short of skilled labor. 这个国家缺乏熟练工人。 2. He is a member of the Labor Party. 他是一名工党党员。 3. The cardinal idea of the Labor Party\'s political thought is that all people should be equal. 工党政治思想的要点是人人平等。 4. Their labor efficiency is very high. 他们的工作效率很高。 5. They figured why should they labor when there was no payoff. 他们认为没有回报为何要去努力工作。 6. The intent is to limit the entry of immigrant labor. 目的是限制移民劳工的进入。', '名词: laborer 过去式: labored 过去分词: labored 现在分词: laboring 第三人称单数: labors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contradict', '[ˌkɒntrə\'dɪkt]', 'vt.反驳；与 ... 矛盾', '1. He did not contradict his attorney\'s comment. 他没有反驳律师的意见。 2. She doesn\'t like to contradict her husband in public. 她不愿在众人面前反驳她丈夫。 3. Don\'t contradict your father. 别和你父亲犟嘴。 4. The report contradicts what we heard yesterday. 这个报道与我们昨天听到的有矛盾。', '形容词: contradictable 名词: contradicter 过去式: contradicted 过去分词: contradicted 现在分词: contradicting 第三人称单数: contradicts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('antique', '[æn\'tiːk]', 'adj.古代的；古老的；过时的 n.古董；古物', '1. The antique table went to the lady in the pink hat. 这张古董桌子卖给那位戴粉红色帽子的女士了。 2. In the museum we saw many antique plates. 我们在博物馆看到了很多古时候的盘子. 3. The antique furniture was made in 1700. 这件古老的家具是1700年制造的。 4. She wore an antique gown to the costume party. 她穿着一件过时的长袍参加化妆舞会。 5. The value of that antique is inestimable. 那件古董的价值无法估计。', '副词: antiquely 名词: antiqueness 过去式: antiqued 过去分词: antiqued 现在分词: antiquing 第三人称单数: antiques');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kick', '[kɪk]', 'v.踢；反冲 n.踢；反冲；后座力', '1. That horse kicked me. 那匹马踢了我。 2. It\'s not fair to kick another player in football. 足球比赛中不允许踢另一位球员。 3. The rifle kicked my shoulder when I fired it. 我开了一枪后，步枪反弹到我肩上 4. The bruise was caused by a kick. 这伤痕是脚踢的。', '过去式: kicked 过去分词: kicked 现在分词: kicking 第三人称单数: kicks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dictate', '[\'dɪkteɪt]', 'vi.听写 vt.口授；规定；决定，影响 n.命令，支配，主宰；指挥；指令', '1. The teacher dictated a passage to the class. 老师给全班同学听写一段文章。 2. He was dictating a letter to his secretary. 他在向秘书口授信稿。 3. He can\'t write but he can dictate. 他不会写但会说。 4. Businessmen often dictate their letters. 商人常口授信稿令人笔录。 5. If I had the dictatorial power in a dictatorship, I will dictate those IT be kept in detention for appearing too pretentious. 我假如拥有独裁政治的专断权，我会命令把她关起来，罪名是外表炫耀做作。', '过去式: dictated 过去分词: dictated 现在分词: dictating 第三人称单数: dictates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transfer', '[træns\'fɜːr]', 'v.转移；调任；转乘 n.迁移；移动；换车；汇兑', '1. The exhibition was transferred to another city two days later. 两天后,这个展会转移到另外一个城市。 2. She has been transferred to another department. 她已被调往另一个部门。 3. I took the subway and then transferred to the bus. 我搭乘地铁然后再改乘公共汽车。 4. Our company will have a transfer to London. 我们公司将迁往伦敦。', '形容词: transferable 名词: transferability 过去式: transferred 过去分词: transferred 现在分词: transferring 第三人称单数: transfers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('export', '[\'ekspɔːrt]', 'n.输出；出口；输出品；输出存储器的信息 v.输出；出口；带走，运走；从存储器输出信息', '1. Prohibition was laid on the export of coal. 禁止煤炭输出。 2. The company\'s gearing up for the big export drive. 公司正为大规模输出作好准备。 3. Consultancy, insurance and tourism are also parts of the export trade. 咨询,保险及旅游也是出口贸易的一部分。 4. Export had suffered during the last six months. 前6个月内，出口已蒙受损失。 5. The blood can also export waste products from the tissues. 血液还能从身体组织里输出废物。', '形容词: exportable 名词: exportability 过去式: exported 过去分词: exported 现在分词: exporting 第三人称单数: exports');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reveal', '[rɪ\'viːl]', 'vt.显示；透露；揭示；展现 n.(外墙与门或窗之间的)窗侧；门侧；(汽车的)窗框', '1. Several withered trees on the sides of the road reveal the desolation here. 道路两旁的几棵枯木显示出这里的荒凉。 2. His deed revealed him to be a kind man. 他的行为显示他是个好心的人。 3. The journalist did not want to reveal the identity of his informant. 那个新闻工作者不想透露消息提供人的身分。 4. He would not reveal what decisions had been reached. 他不肯透露做出了什么决定。', '形容词: revealable 名词: revealer 过去式: revealed 过去分词: revealed 现在分词: revealing 第三人称单数: reveals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('librarian', '[laɪ\'breriən]', 'n.图书管理员；图书馆学专家；图书馆馆长', '1. The librarian saved the rare books from the fire. 这位图书管理员从火中救出了一些珍本书。', '名词: librarianship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alone', '[ə\'loʊn]', 'adj.单独的；独自一人的；孤单的 adv.独自地；仅仅', '1. Tom is not alone in finding Rick hard to work with. 并不只是汤姆一人认为和里克难以共事。 2. I was alone in the classroom. 我独自在教室里。 3. To tell you the truth, I don\'t feel like being alone tonight. 说实话,我今晚不想孤单一人。 4. After tea I wandered alone about the town. 吃过下午茶,我独自在城里漫步。', '名词: aloneness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('queue', '[kjuː]', 'n.长队；行列；辫子 v.排队', '1. People had to stand in a queue for hours to buy a ticket. 人们买票得排几小时的队。 2. At the head of the queue was an old woman. 在队列的前面有一个老妇人。 3. It was quite easy to tell that this queue was false. 很容易看出这个辫子是假的。 4. We queued up for the bus. 我们排队等公共汽车。', '过去式: queued 过去分词: queued 现在分词: queuing 第三人称单数: queues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scarce', '[skers]', 'adj.缺乏的；不足的；稀少的；罕见的 adv.勉强', '1. Food and fuel were scarce in this region. 这地区食物和燃料都很缺乏。 2. Firewood is scarce in many parts of the world. 世界上很多地区都缺乏木材。 3. Food commands a higher price when it is scarce. 食物(供应)不足时，售价较高。 4. As Singapore is a small island, land is scarce. 新加坡是一个小岛,土地稀有。 5. I could scarce believe my eyes. 我几乎不敢相信自己的眼睛。', '比较级: scarcer 最高级: scarcest 名词: scarceness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('move', '[muːv]', 'n.移动；步骤；迁居；动作 vt.推动；使移动；使 ... 感动；提议 vi.移动；搬家；采取行动', '1. The army is on the move. 军队在移动。 2. This move is now in preparation. 这一步骤，目前正在准备中。 3. Their move to Latin America was a leap in the dark. 他们迁居拉丁美洲是件冒险的事。 4. Evans is a rare dancer, whose moves are so elegant. 伊万是个杰出的舞者，他的动作非常优美。 5. Give me a place to stand and I will move the world. 给我一个支点，我会推动地球。 6. Give it a hard push, then it will move. 用力推一下，就能使它移动。', '过去式: moved 过去分词: moved 现在分词: moving 第三人称单数: moves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accept', '[ək\'sept]', 'vt.接受；同意；承担(责任等) vi.接受', '1. We gave him a present,but he did not accept it. 我们给他一件礼物,但他不肯接受。 2. She is too independent to accept charity. 她很强调自力更生,不肯接受赈济。 3. she accepted the judge\'s decision. 她同意了法官的判决。 4. They accepted responsibility for the accident. 他们承认了对这次事故所负的责任。 5. She offered him a lift and he accepted. 她请他坐她的车，他就领情了。', '过去式: accepted 过去分词: accepted 现在分词: accepting 第三人称单数: accepts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('menace', '[\'menəs]', 'n.威胁；恐吓；<口>讨厌的人（物） v.威吓；威胁', '1. These weapons are a menace to world peace. 这些武器是对世界和平的威胁。 2. The man\'s lunatic behavior is a menace to society. 那个人的疯狂行为构成对社会的威胁。 3. That film creates an atmosphere of menace. 那部影片营造出吓人的气氛。 4. Your vicious dog is menacing my cat! 你那条恶狗对我家的猫太凶了！', '副词: menacingly 名词: menacer 过去式: menaced 过去分词: menaced 现在分词: menacing 第三人称单数: menaces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wreath', '[riːθ]', 'n.花圈；花环；花冠', '1. A group of student placed a wreath at the tomb of the national hero. 一群学生在那位民族英雄墓前献上花圈。 2. They twisted flowers into a wreath. 他们用花编成了一个花圈。 3. They put some wreaths on the ground. 他们把一些花环放在地上。 4. I ordered a wreath from the florist. 我从花店定购了一个花冠。', '名词复数: wreaths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cut', '[kʌt]', 'v.切；割；剪；削减；伤害；切牌 n.切口；切；式样；剪辑', '1. This knife is not sharp enough to cut the steak. 这把刀子不够利,无法切牛排。 2. Don\'t cut your finger on the broken glass. 别让碎玻璃割伤你的手。 3. Face round, please, so that I can cut your hair at the back. 转一下头, 好让我可以剪你后面的头发。 4. Please cut out the expense in order to save the money. 为了节省钱,请削减开支。 5. His cheek was badly scarred by a knife cut. 他的面颊上留有严重的刀疤。', '形容词: cuttable 过去式: cut 过去分词: cut 现在分词: cutting 第三人称单数: cuts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('major', '[\'meɪdʒər]', 'adj.较多的；主要的；严重的；(音乐)大调的 n.成年人；主修（科目）；陆军少校；举足轻重者 v.主修', '1. The city holds the major portion of the population in the country. 那个城市聚集了全国大部分人口。 2. Popular education is one of our major objectives. 民众教育是我们的主要目标之一。 3. This quartet represents a major new trend in modern music. 这首四重奏的曲子反映了现代音乐中一种主要的新趋向。 4. We have encountered major problems. 我们已遇到重大的问题。 5. Majors should take more responsibilities and be more intelligent in handling personal relations. 成年人要承担更多的责任,在处理人际关系中也要变得更急灵活。 6. She majored in maths and physics at university. 她在大学期间主修数学和物理。', '过去式: majored 过去分词: majored 现在分词: majoring 第三人称单数: majors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('earnest', '[\'ɜːrnɪst]', 'adj.认真的；真诚的 n.定金；预示；保证 n.认真；诚挚', '1. I\'m sure he was earnest when he said he would come. 我相信他说他会来是认真的。 2. He is a good, earnest, diligent student. 他是一个认真勤奋的好学生。 3. I strive to live each day with earnest gratitude. 我努力使生活的每一天都充满真诚的感激。 4. Earnest was legally unnecessary. 法律上并不要求必须有定金。 5. She spoke half in sport, half in earnest. 她半开玩笑半认真地说。', '副词: earnestly 名词: earnestness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tropic', '[\'trɑːpɪk]', 'n.回归线；热带 adj.热带的', '1. The outside temperature in countries outside the Tropic belt is too volatile and too cold to allow the tree to develop. 在这条回归线带外边的国家的室外温度太易变并且太冷不能允许树生长。 2. She sorted out her things for tropic travel. 她整理热带旅行的东西。 3. The tropic sun glared down on us all day. 热带的太阳整日灼晒着我们。 4. The tropic sun glared down on us all day. 热带的太阳整日灼晒着我们。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whatsoever', '[ˌwɒtsoʊ\'evə]', 'adv.任何(用于否定句中以加强语气) pron.无论什么 adj.无论什么的', '1. I see no objection whatsoever. 我没有任何异议。 2. The police found no suspicious document whatsoever. 警察未发现任何可怀疑的文件。 3. You must do whatsoever is best for you. 什么对你最有利你就做什么。 4. Take whatsoever measures you consider best. 采取任何你认为最好的措施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lawn', '[lɔːn]', 'n.草坪；草地', '1. My mother asked me to mow the lawn. 妈妈让我去剪草坪。 2. Let\'s have tea on the lawn. 我们到草坪上去喝茶吧。 3. Moles dug tunnels under the lawn. 鼹鼠在草地下面打洞。 4. The reception was held in a pavilion on the lawn. 招待会在草地中的亭子里举行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('monotonous', '[mə\'nɑːtənəs]', 'adj.单调的', '1. The preacher\'s monotonous voice put me to sleep. 传教士单调的声音催我入眠。 2. His monotonous whistling grated on her nerves. 他单调的口哨声令她的神经受不了。', '副词: monotonously 名词: monotonousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('promote', '[prə\'moʊt]', 'vt.促进；提升；升迁；发起；促销，推销', '1. They discussed how to promote cooperation between the two countries. 他们讨论如何促进两国间的合作。 2. He has been promoted to general manager. 他已被提升为总经理。 3. He failed to get promoted for lack of resolution. 他因缺乏果断力而未能得到升迁。 4. He promoted a campaign to remind the public of protecting the wildlife. 他发起了一项旨在提醒人们保护野生动物的活动。', '形容词: promotable 名词: promotability 过去式: promoted 过去分词: promoted 现在分词: promoting 第三人称单数: promotes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gauge', '[ɡeɪdʒ]', 'n.测量仪器；测量标准；（铁道的）轨距；（钢丝等的）直径；（枪管的）口径 v.估计；判断；测量', '1. The fuel gauges dropped swiftly. 燃料表指针迅速下降。 2. What gauge of wire should we use for this job? 我们干这活应该用多大号的铅丝? 3. This is a narrow-gauge railway. 这是一条窄轨铁路。 4. We must gauge the diameter of wire first. 我们必须先测量电线的直径。 5. It was difficult to gauge how people would respond. 大家的反应如何难以估计。', '形容词: gaugeable 过去式: gauged/gaged 过去分词: gauged/gaged 现在分词: gauging/gaging 第三人称单数: gauges/gages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('line', '[laɪn]', 'n.线；界线；皱纹；路线；航线；行；台词；行业；绳子；家族 v.排队；画线；加衬里', '1. One line cuts another at right angles. 一条线与另一条线成直角相交。 2. The ball went over the line. 球越线出界了。 3. The line of the two countries is too vague. 这两个国家的界线太模糊了。 4. He has fine lines around his eyes. 他的眼睛周围有细细的皱纹。 5. Please line up one after another. 请按顺序排队。', '过去式: lined 过去分词: lined 现在分词: lining 第三人称单数: lines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('application', '[ˌæplɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.应用；申请；专心；应用程序', '1. The application of new scientific discoveries to industrial production methods usually increases efficiency. 把新的科学发现运用到工业生产上,通常可以提高效率。 2. I didn\'t receive an acknowledgement of my application. 对我的申请,我还没有收到复信告知收悉。 3. The manager received twenty applications for the post. 经理收到了二十份求职申请书。 4. Patience and application will carry us through. 忍耐和专心会使我们度过难关。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('orthodox', '[\'ɔːrθədɑːks]', 'adj.正统的；传统的；东正教的', '1. He is very orthodox in his views. 他的观点十分正统。 2. The young generation today don\'t like orthodox teaching. 当今的年轻一代不喜欢正统的说教。 3. Orthodox Christian churches often have elaborate steeples. 传统的基督教堂都有精致的尖塔。 4. The restaurant offers the orthodox Christmas dinner of turkey. 这个餐馆供应传统的圣诞火鸡餐。', '副词: orthodoxly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('difficult', '[\'dɪfɪkəlt]', 'adj.困难的；艰难的；(人)难对付的；不易相处的', '1. The quest for gold was difficult. 寻找金矿是很困难的。 2. The child is going through a difficult phase. 那孩子正经历困难的阶段。 3. She handled a difficult argument skilfully. 她巧妙地应付了一场艰难的辩论。 4. She is just being difficult. 她正在闹别扭呢。', '副词: difficultly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('passer-by', '[\'pɑːsə baɪ]', 'n.过路人；经过者', '1. The purse was picked up by a passer. 钱包被一个过路人捡到了。 2. Somebody passing by asked me the way to the post office. 一个过路人问我去邮局怎么走。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('salt', '[sɔːlt]', 'n.盐；刺激；盐类 vt.用盐腌；加盐于', '1. Salt water is more buoyant than fresh water. 盐水比淡水浮力大。 2. He had spoiled the soup by putting in too much salt. 他往汤里放盐太多，把汤给糟蹋了。 3. Adventure is the salt of life to some people. 冒险对某些人来说是生活中的刺激。 4. An acid can react with a base to form a salt. 酸可以和碱起反应而生成盐。 5. They salted down most of the meat for their later use. 他们将大部分肉用盐腌起来，以备日后用。', '过去式: salted 过去分词: salted 现在分词: salting 第三人称单数: salts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('endurance', '[ɪn\'dʊrəns]', 'n.忍耐；忍耐力；耐性', '1. She exhibited great powers of endurance during the climb. 她在攀登过程中表现出极大的耐力。 2. I honour endurance, perseverance, industry, talent. 我尊敬忍耐、坚毅，勤劳、才干。 3. Her endurance of pain was incredible. 她对痛苦的忍耐力令人难以置信。 4. She was outstanding where endurance was called for. 她在需要忍耐力的地方表现优异。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kidnap', '[\'kɪdnæp]', 'v.绑架', '1. Police have uncovered a plot to kidnap the President\'s son. 警方已侦破一起绑架总统之子的阴谋。 2. If you improve security at embassies, they kidnap businessmen. 如果你加强了大使馆的安全防范，他们就绑架商人。', '名词: kidnapper 过去式: kidnapped/kidnaped 过去分词: kidnapped/kidnaped 现在分词: kidnapping/kidnaping 第三人称单数: kidnaps/kidnaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('component', '[kəm\'poʊnənt]', 'n.零部件；元件；组成部分；成分 adj.组成的；构成的', '1. The factory supplies components for the car industry. 该工厂向汽车业供应零部件。 2. Each of the components is useful in its degree. 每一个元件都各有程度不同的用处。 3. The militia is a component of the state\'s armed forces. 民兵是国家武装力量的组成部分。 4. A chemist can seperate a medicine into its components. 化学家能把一种药物的各种成分分解出来。 5. Can you resolve it into its component elements? 你能把它分解为组成它的元素吗?', '形容词: componential');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('greedy', '[\'ɡriːdi]', 'adj.贪婪的', '1. He is a greedy capitalist. 他是一个贪婪的资本家。 2. He looked at the shop window with greedy eyes. 他用贪婪的眼光看着商店的橱窗。', '副词: greedily 比较级: greedier 最高级: greediest 名词: greediness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soldier', '[\'soʊldʒər]', 'n.士兵；军人 vi.当兵；坚持做', '1. The soldier received a serious wound on the chest. 这名士兵胸部受了重伤。 2. The trade of the soldier is war. 士兵的职业是打仗。 3. I believe he is meant to be a soldier. 我相信他天生是要当军人的。 4. A faint-hearted person should not be a soldier. 懦弱的人不应该当兵。', '过去式: soldiered 过去分词: soldiered 现在分词: soldiering 第三人称单数: soldiers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sound', '[saʊnd]', 'n.声音；嘈杂声；音乐风格；曲调；印象；感觉；海峡；鱼鳔；探针 v.听起来；感觉起来；发出声音；发音；探测深度；探询 adj.有效的；合理的；可靠的；全面的；健康的；完好的；酣睡的；严厉的 adv.酣畅地', '1. The man was gone: his footsteps made no sound. 那人走了,他的脚步没有发出一点声音。 2. I caught a curious sound in the neighboring room. 我听到隔壁房间里有奇怪的响声。 3. He plays an original jazz-gospel sound. 他演奏了一曲自己独创的爵士福音。 4. The bell gave forth a peasant, lingering sound. 钟奏起了悠扬悦耳的曲调。 5. You sound a little down in dumps. 你听起来好象情绪有点低落。 6. There are possible risks, but nonetheless, we feel it\'s a sound investment. 有可能存在危险,但是我们仍然感到这是可靠的投资。 7. He slept sound in his mother\'s cradle song. 他在母亲唱的摇篮曲中酣然入睡。', '形容词: soundable 副词: soundly 比较级: sounder 最高级: soundest 名词: soundness 过去式: sounded 过去分词: sounded 现在分词: sounding 第三人称单数: sounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('construction', '[kən\'strʌkʃn]', 'n.建设；结构；建筑物；建造；构造；解释', '1. China is striding ahead in her economic construction. 中国正在经济建设方面大步前进。 2. It is an object of simple construction. 它是一个简单结构的物体。 3. The cathedral is a fantastic modern construction. 那个教堂是奇特的现代建筑。 4. The new airport is still under construction. 新机场仍在修建中。', '形容词: constructional 副词: constructionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('confirm', '[kən\'fɜːrm]', 'v.证实；批准；确定', '1. His letter confirmed everything. 他的信证实了一切。 2. The treaty was confirmed by the president. 条约已被总统批准。 3. Could you confirm the dispatch date? 您可以确定发货日期吗?', '形容词: confirmable 名词: confirmability 过去式: confirmed 过去分词: confirmed 现在分词: confirming 第三人称单数: confirms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stool', '[stuːl]', 'n.凳子；搁脚凳；便桶；大便 vi.引诱', '1. He wreathed his legs about the stool. 他用双腿围住凳子。 2. The new styled school-bag can double as a stool. 这种新式书包可兼做凳子。 3. You can have the piano for 60, and I\'ll throw in the stool as well. 这架钢琴可以卖给你 60 英镑，琴凳我奉送。 4. He goes to stool twice a day. 他每天大便两次。', '过去式: stooled 过去分词: stooled 现在分词: stooling 第三人称单数: stools');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mushroom', '[\'mʌʃrʊm]', 'n.蘑菇；菌菇状物；暴发户 vi.采蘑菇；雨后春笋般涌现；迅速增加', '1. Some mushrooms are poisonous. 有些蘑菇有毒。 2. I gathered many mushrooms after rain. 雨后我采了很多蘑菇。 3. The mushroom cloud of the A-bomb hung over the desert again. 原子弹爆炸的蘑菇云再度笼罩在沙漠的上空。 4. Mushroom clouds appear after nuclear explosions. 核弹爆炸后会产生蘑菇云。 5. Let\'s go mushrooming. 我们采蘑菇去吧。', '过去式: mushroomed 过去分词: mushroomed 现在分词: mushrooming 第三人称单数: mushrooms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suspicious', '[sə\'spɪʃəs]', 'adj.可疑的；多疑的', '1. I am suspicious of his intentions. 我怀疑他的用意。 2. Two suspicious characters were brought in. 逮捕了两名嫌疑犯。 3. I feel suspicious about the truth of the account. 我对于这帐目的真实性感到怀疑。 4. The locals tend to be suspicious of strangers. 当地人对陌生人往往有戒心。', '副词: suspiciously 名词: suspiciousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dizzy', '[\'dɪzi]', 'adj.晕眩的；(速度)极快的；困惑的 vt.使晕眩；使困惑', '1. The airplane climbed to a dizzy height. 飞机爬到令人头晕目眩的高度。 2. Riding on merry-go-round makes me feel dizzy. 骑木马让我觉得眩晕。 3. Prices keep rising at a dizzy rate. 物价以极快的速度不断上涨。 4. He likes to drive at a dizzy speed. 他喜欢开快车。 5. The old woman was dizzied by the strong wind. 那位老太太被风吹得头昏眼花。', '副词: dizzily 比较级: dizzier 最高级: dizziest 名词: dizziness 过去式: dizzied 过去分词: dizzied 现在分词: dizzying 第三人称单数: dizzies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('four', '[fɔːr]', 'num.四', '1. Six minus two equals four. 六减去二等于四。 2. This street is four times shorter than that one. 这条街道比那条短四倍。 3. He arranged his speech under four main heads. 他把发言内容归纳成四个主要方面。 4. The leap year comes around once in four years. 每四年有一个闰年。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grape', '[ɡreɪp]', 'n.葡萄；葡萄树；深紫色；[军]葡萄弹', '1. The loser\'s scorn for the award is pure sour grape. 失败者对奖品的轻视纯粹是吃不到葡萄说葡萄酸。 2. Sour grape can never make sweet wine. 酸葡萄酿不出甜酒。 3. The sun shines through the grape-leaves. 太阳从葡萄树叶中穿过。 4. We need this piece of cloth to be grape. 我们需要这块布是深紫色的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weather', '[\'weðər]', 'n.天气；气象；境遇 vt.使风化；经受住；使日晒雨淋 vi.风化；褪色；经受风雨 adj.上风的；天气预报的', '1. What is the weather like today? 今天天气情况怎样？ 2. The meteorologist drew a picture of the weather. 气象学者画了一张气象图。 3. The past years had known him in many weathers. 过去的岁月里,他起起落落。 4. The rocks on the mountain have to be weathered by wind and water. 山上的岩石得经受风化和水蚀。 5. The paint on the walls had weathered. 墙壁上的涂料已经风干了。 6. Fill in the form below about the weather report. 续下面关于天气预报的表格。', '过去式: weathered 过去分词: weathered 现在分词: weathering 第三人称单数: weathers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rough', '[rʌf]', 'adj.粗糙的；粗略的，大概的；粗暴的；艰难的；讨厌的；不适的；汹涌的 adv.粗糙地；粗暴地 n.粗制品；暴徒；高低不平的路面 vt.使粗糙；殴打；草拟', '1. The rough road made the car vibrate. 崎岖不平的道路使车颠簸得很厉害。 2. You\'d better give us a rough idea of your price. 您最好给我们一个粗略的价格。 3. It is only a rough guide to ideal weight. 这只是一个实现理想体重的粗略的办法。 4. They complained rough handling by the police. 他们抱怨受到警察粗野的对待。 5. He is now able to play rough and tumble with the other kids. 现在他可以粗暴地摔倒其他孩子了。 6. I think that new singer is a diamond in the rough. 我觉得那个新歌手是块未经雕琢的玉。 7. Micro-exfoliators help slough away rough, dull, uneven skin for a more radiant complexion. 细腻的磨砂颗粒帮助去除被溶解的角质，使粗糙晦暗不均匀的皮肤重现柔嫩和光泽。', '副词: roughly 比较级: rougher 最高级: roughest 名词: rougher 过去式: roughed 过去分词: roughed 现在分词: roughing 第三人称单数: roughs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expectation', '[ˌekspek\'teɪʃn]', 'n.预料；期望', '1. It is really out of my expectation. 这真是出乎我的意料。 2. There\'s no expectation of snow tonight. 今晚预料无雪. 3. His parents have great expectations for his future. 他父母对他的前途深寄厚望。 4. She had high expectations of what university had to offer. 她对大学所能给她提供的一切期望很高.', '形容词: expectational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wholly', '[\'hoʊlli]', 'adv.完全地；全部地；一概', '1. I wholly stand for you. 我完全支持你。 2. I am wholly immersed in this business at present. 我目前完全投入于这工作。 3. You are not wholly to blame for the accident. 你不应承担事故的全部责任。 4. He doesn\'t wholly agree to the plan. 他并不完全同意这项计划。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extensive', '[ɪk\'stensɪv]', 'adj.广泛的；广阔的；广大的；大量的', '1. The device had undergone extensive testing. 这种装置经受过广泛的试验。 2. I have benefited a lot from extensive reading. 广泛的阅读使我受益匪浅。 3. The teacher had both extensive knowledge and profound scholarship. 先生的学问博大精深。 4. The mansion has extensive grounds. 这大厦四周的庭园广阔。', '副词: extensively 名词: extensiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gang', '[ɡæŋ]', 'n.一群；一伙；(歹徒等的)一帮 v.结成一伙；结伙袭击', '1. A gang of workmen were repairing the road. 一群工人在修路。 2. The phone box was vandalized by a gang of youths. 那电话亭被一群少年歹徒故意破坏了。 3. The whole gang from the office went to a clambake. 办公室的一伙人去聚会。 4. He was badly beaten up by a gang of thugs. 他被一帮暴徒打得死去活来。 5. Several companies gang up to raise prices. 几家大公司串通一气抬高物价。', '过去式: ganged 过去分词: ganged 现在分词: ganging 第三人称单数: gangs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obey', '[ə\'beɪ]', 'v.服从；遵守；顺从；听从', '1. Soldiers are expected to obey their orders without question. 军人应当绝对服从命令。 2. We should obey the law. 我们应当遵守法律。 3. The abbot told him to obey the rules. 修道院院长告诉他要遵守规定。 4. We must obey the decencies and attend the funeral. 我们要遵照礼仪参加葬礼。', '名词: obeyer 过去式: obeyed 过去分词: obeyed 现在分词: obeying 第三人称单数: obeys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eve', '[iːv]', 'n.（重大节日的）前夜；前夕 Eve. n.夏娃（圣经中的第一个女人）', '1. What will they do on Christmas Eve? 他们在圣诞夜将做什么事？ 2. The country was on the eve of the First Revolution. 当时全国处于第一次革命的前夜。 3. We went to the church to celebrate Christmas Eve. 我们去教堂庆祝圣诞前夕。 4. He gave up on the eve of success. 他在大功告成之前放弃了。 5. Eve tempted Adam and he fell. 夏娃诱惑亚当，结果他犯了罪。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('humor', '[\'hju:mə]', 'n.幽默；诙谐；心情 vt.迁就；顺应', '1. The black humor is overwhelming in that novel. 那部小说有太多荒诞的幽默。 2. I like your sense of humor. 我喜欢你的幽默感。 3. His new novel is tinged with thinnish humor. 他的新小说略带诙谐。 4. She smiled him into a good humor. 她对他微笑使他心情好转。 5. It\'s not always wise to humor a small child. 迁就小孩子不总是明智的。', '过去式: humored 过去分词: humored 现在分词: humoring 第三人称单数: humors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('metal', '[\'metl]', 'n.金属；合金；玻璃液 vt.(以金属)覆盖、装配', '1. Copper and gold are both metals. 铜和金都是金属。 2. Wood floats on the water but metal sinks. 木头漂在水面上,而金属却下沉。 3. They cut holes on the sheet of metal with a punch press. 他们用冲床在金属板上打孔。 4. The frame is made of metal. 框子是用金属做的。 5. This rough track will soon be a metalled road. 这条坑坑洼洼的路不久就要铺上碎石了。', '过去式: metaled/metalled 过去分词: metaled/metalled 现在分词: metaling/metalling 第三人称单数: metals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weep', '[wiːp]', 'v.流泪；哭泣；悲叹；渗出 n.哭泣；<俚>眼泪', '1. She wept bitter tears over her lost youth. 她为自己逝去的青春痛苦地流泪。 2. It is better to laugh than (to) weep. 笑比哭好。 3. I weep for the loss of your husband. 我为你失去丈夫而哭泣。 4. The girl weep at the painful news. 那姑娘因悲痛的消息而哭泣。 5. good weep would probably make you feel better. 你痛痛快快哭上阵也许就好受些了。', '过去式: wept 过去分词: wept 现在分词: weeping 第三人称单数: weeps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reader', '[\'riːdər]', 'n.读者；读物；读本', '1. He writes with the reader in mind. 他写作时把读者放在心上。 2. I am a regular reader of this newspaper. 我是这份报纸的长期读者。 3. This reader is supplementary to the textbook. 这本读物是补充教科书的。 4. Your course reader will have most of the required articles and book chapters. 课程读物包含大部分的必读书籍和章节。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tidy', '[\'taɪdi]', 'adj.整齐的；整洁的；<口>相当大的 vt.整理；使整洁 vi.整理；收拾', '1. She keeps her house very tidy. 她保持她的住所整整齐齐。 2. They sat in her neat and tidy kitchen. 他们坐在她那干净整齐的厨房里。 3. He has a tidy mind. 他的思维有条理。 4. Her clothes were clean and tidy. 她的衣服干净整洁。 5. His room is in a clutter so I have to tidy it up. 他的房间乱七八糟的，我不得不整理一下。 6. You\'d better tidy up before the guests arrive. 客人们到达前,你最好先把东西整理一下。', '副词: tidily 比较级: tidier 最高级: tidiest 名词: tidiness 名词复数: tidies 过去式: tidied 过去分词: tidied 现在分词: tidying 第三人称单数: tidies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('moreover', '[mɔːr\'oʊvər]', 'adv.此外；而且', '1. He was, moreover, a poet of promise. 此外，他还是一个有前途的诗人。 2. It was, moreover, a waste of time. 此外,那是浪费时间。 3. Moreover,I will thank all the people who helped me. 此外，我要感谢所有帮助过我的人。 4. I don\'t like skating, moreover, the ice is too thin. 我不喜欢滑冰，而且冰又太薄。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('finding', '[\'faɪndɪŋ]', 'n.调查(或研究)的结果；[律] 裁决 find的现在分词.', '1. The finding is based on such an inquiry. 基于如上调查所得出的发现', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('club', '[klʌb]', 'n.俱乐部；棍棒；(扑克牌中)梅花 v.用棍棒打；分担花费；凑钱；泡夜总会', '1. The tennis club has organized a dance. 网球俱乐部组织了一次舞会。 2. He is an active member of the school\'s stamp club. 他是学校集邮俱乐部的一名活跃会员。 3. I was a slave under club and fist. 在他们的棍棒和拳脚下，我就是一个奴隶。 4. You can see the king of club is the winning play. 你可以看出来打梅花K是赢牌的一招。 5. He was clubbed to death with a butt of a gun. 他是被人用枪托殴打致死的。', '过去式: clubbed 过去分词: clubbed 现在分词: clubbing 第三人称单数: clubs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fan', '[fæn]', 'n.风扇；扇子；扇形物 n.迷；狂热爱好者 vt.扇；展开扇形；煽动 vi.成扇形；[棒]三振出局', '1. We have an extractor fan in the kitchen to get rid of the smell of cooking. 我们的厨房里有台排气扇，用来消除油烟。 2. Please turn the electric fan on. 请打开电风扇。 3. She glanced shyly at him from behind her fan. 她羞怯地从她的扇子后面看了他一眼。 4. My boss is a football fan. 我的上司是一位足球迷。 5. We fanned the fire to make it burn brighter. 我们把炉火扇得更旺。 6. The soldiers fanned out across the hillside in their search for the man. 士兵们在山腰上成扇形散开，搜索那个男人。', '过去式: fanned 过去分词: fanned 现在分词: fanning 第三人称单数: fans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exempt', '[ɪɡ\'zempt]', 'adj.免除的 vt.免除 n.免税者；被免除义务者', '1. He is exempt from military service. 他免服兵役。 2. These houses are exempt from paying rates. 这些房子是免付捐税的。 3. Poor eyesight will exempt you from military service. 视力不佳将使你免服兵役。 4. We hope you will exempt us from taxes. 希望贵方能给予我们免征关税待遇。', '形容词: exemptible 过去式: exempted 过去分词: exempted 现在分词: exempting 第三人称单数: exempts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pig', '[pɪɡ]', 'n.猪；猪肉；像猪一样的人 v.生小猪', '1. A pig is a domestic animal. 猪是一种家畜。 2. The farmer keeps hundreds of pigs on his farm. 那个农场主在他的农场里养了几百头猪。 3. The snout of the pig you drew on the picture is too long. 这幅画上你画的猪鼻子太长了。 4. Days passed,and nothing more was said about the roast pig. 好几天过去了，再没提起考猪肉的事儿。', '过去式: pigged 过去分词: pigged 现在分词: pigging 第三人称单数: pigs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impression', '[ɪm\'preʃn]', 'n.印象；感觉；模仿 n.印迹；印刷', '1. Her gentleness has given me a deep impression. 她的亲切给我留下了很深的印象。 2. I am surprised you\'ve got an unfavorable impression of him. 我很惊讶你对他印象不佳。 3. I had the impression that your boy hates school. 我感觉你的孩子不喜欢去上学。 4. The students did some marvellous impressions of the teachers at the end-of-term party. 在期末联欢会上,学生惟妙惟肖地模仿起了教师。 5. The well-printed book has a sharp, clean impression. 印刷良好的书籍有明显而清楚的印痕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('electric', '[ɪ\'lektrɪk]', 'adj.电的；电动的；带电的；刺激的 n.电动产品', '1. They still live in the houses without electric lights. 他们仍然住在没有电灯的房子里。 2. The solar cell can convert the energy of sunlight into electric energy. 太阳能电池能把阳光的能量转化为电能。 3. He uses an electric razor for shaving. 他用一把电动刮脸刀刮脸。 4. He bought an electric hair-drier for Mary. 他给玛丽买了一个电吹风。 5. The lawn mower is an electric. 割草机是电动的机器。', '副词: electrically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unfortunately', '[ʌn\'fɔːrtʃənətli]', 'adv.不幸地；遗憾地', '1. Unfortunately, I missed the last train. 我不幸错过了末班火车。 2. Unfortunately, I hurt my knee when I fell down on the ice. 真不幸，我在冰上摔倒时摔伤了膝盖。 3. Unfortunately I am not aware of that. 遗憾的是，我不知道此事。 4. Unfortunately, the restaurant he recommended fell far short of our expectations. 遗憾的是,他推荐的餐厅与我们心目中的相去甚远。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hint', '[hɪnt]', 'n.暗示 v.暗示；示意', '1. There were subtle hints in his letter. 他的信中有些微妙的暗示。 2. I hinted at his imprudence,his folly,but he did not take my hint. 我暗示他的轻率,他的愚蠢,但他没有觉察我的暗示。 3. He did not drop any hint, nor did his secretary. 他没有作任何暗示,他的秘书也没有。 4. The possibility of an early election has been hinted at. 已经有迹象表明可能提前进行选举。', '名词: hinter 过去式: hinted 过去分词: hinted 现在分词: hinting 第三人称单数: hints');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spend', '[spend]', 'n.预算；花销 v.花费；浪费；度过；用尽（气力等）', '1. The average spend on higher education was 55 pounds per head. 用于高等教育的平均支出是每人55英镑。 2. The new law will put a lid on government spend. 新法律将限制政府开支。 3. The time I spend in commuting every day adds up to three hours. 我每天上下班乘车花费的时间加起来有3个小时。 4. You really shouldn\'t spend so much effort on it. 你真不该在这件事上花费这么大的精力。', '形容词: spendable 名词: spender 过去式: spent 过去分词: spent 现在分词: spending 第三人称单数: spends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beast', '[biːst]', 'n.兽；畜牲', '1. The lion is called the king of beasts. 狮子号称百兽之王。 2. The hunters blocked up the hole of the beast. 猎人堵住了兽穴。 3. He put the beast out and headed home. 他把这只畜牲丢下，掉头就回家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('internal', '[ɪn\'tɜːrnl]', 'adj.国内的；内部的；身内的', '1. They were opposed to foreign involvement in their internal affairs. 他们反对外国参与他们本国内政。 2. He worked in internal trade. 他的工作是做国内贸易。 3. We should make an internal inquiry to find out who is responsible for the it. 我们应进行内部调查,找出对此事承担责任的人。 4. She\'s been having some internal problems. 她一直有些内科疾病。', '副词: internally 名词: internality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('incredible', '[ɪn\'kredəbl]', 'adj.难以置信的；惊人的', '1. I think it\'s incredible. 我认为这是难以置信的。 2. That\'s the most incredible coincidence I\'ve ever heard of! 那是我听说过的最难以置信的巧合！ 3. He showed an incredible indifference to the matter. 他对这件事表现出令人难以置信的淡漠。 4. He has an incredible house! 他有一所极美的房子！', '副词: incredibly 名词: incredibility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beforehand', '[bɪ\'fɔːrhænd]', 'adv.预先；事先；提前', '1. I had made preparations beforehand. 我预先作了准备。 2. He warned me beforehand what to expect. 他预先提醒过我这件事。 3. We were aware of the problem beforehand. 我们事先就知道有这个问题。 4. Actually I meant to notify you beforehand. 实际上我是想事先通知你的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hate', '[heɪt]', 'v.憎恨；厌恶；讨厌 n.憎恨；厌恶', '1. They hate each other. 他们彼此憎恨。 2. I hate to squabble with my wife about money. 我厌恶为钱的事兴太太争吵。 3. The boys hate doing homework on Sundays. 男孩们讨厌在星期日做家庭作业。 4. She hates to be late for work. 她不喜欢上班迟到。 5. She looked at him with hate in her eyes. 她以憎恨的目光看着他。', '名词: hater 过去式: hated 过去分词: hated 现在分词: hating 第三人称单数: hates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('party', '[\'pɑːrti]', 'n.聚会；宴会；政党；一伙人；[律]当事人 vi.开派对', '1. It\'s a pity that you can\'t come to the party. 你不能来参加这次聚会，真可惜。 2. There was a liberal supply of drinks at the party. 那次宴会上有大量饮料供应。 3. The Labour party went out in 1980. 工党于1980年下野。 4. He was admitted to the Party last year. 他去年入党了。 5. That night we partied until dawn. 那晚我们痛饮到天亮', '名词复数: parties 过去式: partied 过去分词: partied 现在分词: partying 第三人称单数: parties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bibliography', '[ˌbɪbli\'ɑːɡrəfi]', 'n.参考书目；文献学', '1. Bibliography usually appears at the end of a book. 参考书目通常在书后列出。 2. The book ought to include a bibliography of the subject. 这本书应包括一份关于这一学科的参考书目。 3. Please include your quotations in the bibliography. 请在参考文献处标明你的引文出处。 4. We have quoted in the bibliography a large number of items. 文献目录中列举了大量文献。', '形容词: bibliographical 副词: bibliographically 名词复数: bibliographies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('foul', '[faʊl]', 'adj.恶臭的；邪恶的；污秽的；恶劣的；犯规的 n.犯规 v.弄脏；妨碍；犯规', '1. He opened the window to let out the foul air. 他打开窗户，放出污浊的空气。 2. The foul weather spoiled our vacation. 恶劣的天气把我们的假期糟踏了。 3. She has a foul temper. 她脾气暴躁。 4. The ball was foul. 这球犯规了。 5. The forward made a foul in the penalty area. 前锋在禁区内犯规了。 6. Owners who allow their dogs to foul the footpath will be fined. 主人若放任狗弄脏人行道将受处罚。', '副词: foully 比较级: fouler 最高级: foulest 名词: foulness 过去式: fouled 过去分词: fouled 现在分词: fouling 第三人称单数: fouls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refusal', '[rɪ\'fjuːzl]', 'n.拒绝；回绝', '1. I translate his silence as a refusal. 我把他的沉默解释为拒绝。 2. She couched her refusal in very polite terms. 她用十分委婉的措辞表示拒绝。 3. Your words amount to a refusal. 你的话等于回绝了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('optional', '[\'ɑːpʃənl]', 'adj.任选的', '1. The insurance cover is optional. 保险范围可以随意选择。 2. It is optional with you. 那是你的自由。 3. The goods are optional, but only one. 这些物品是可以任选的, 但只能选一个。 4. A 4-speed automatic transmission is optional. 四段自动变速器是可自由选择的。', '副词: optionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lane', '[leɪn]', 'n.小路；小巷；行车道；跑道；航道', '1. The lane is the boundary of our land from theirs. 那条小路就是我们这片地与他们那片地的分界线。 2. She drives carefully up the rocky lane. 她驾车小心地从这条很多石头的小路上驶过去。 3. That lane will take you to his house. 你从那条小巷就可以走到他家。 4. The lane was rutted with tyre tracks. 这小巷有车胎轧出的凹痕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('metropolitan', '[ˌmetrə\'pɑːlɪtən]', 'adj.大都市的；大主教区的 n.大都市的居民；大主教', '1. Metropolitan residents are used to fast rhythm. 大都市的居民习惯于快节奏。 2. He can not adjust himself to the pace of metropolitan life. 他适应不了都市生活的节奏。 3. She left the small island and became famous in metropolitan France. 她离开小岛而在法国的大都市中成名。 4. Metropolitan residents are used to fast rhythm. 大都市的居民习惯于快节奏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('residence', '[\'rezɪdəns]', 'n.住宅；住处；居住', '1. I want to insure my residence. 我要为自己的住宅保险。 2. They have a summer residence in the countryside. 他们在乡间有夏季住宅。 3. He went on to his former residence. 他继续向他从前的住所走去。 4. He has applied for a residence permit. 他已申请了居住许可证。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shortcoming', '[\'ʃɔːrtkʌmɪŋ]', 'n.缺点；短处', '1. Not being punctual is his greatest shortcoming. 不守时间是他的最大缺点。 2. Donna is sensible of his shortcoming. 唐纳知道他自己的缺点。 3. No matter who point out our shortcoming, we will correct them. 不管谁指出我们的缺点，我们都改正。 4. If it were not for this shortcoming, he is a fairly good teacher. 要不是有这一缺点，他本是一个相当好的教师。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lure', '[lʊr]', 'vt.诱惑；吸引 n.诱惑；吸引力；饵', '1. The travel brochure lured me into taking a Caribbean vacation. 这本旅游小册子诱使我去加勒比地区度假。 2. The enticement of the big city lure her away from her home. 大城市的种种诱惑吸引了她离家出走。 3. It\'s very difficult to lure talent away from Silicon Valley. 很难将硅谷的人才吸引走。 4. Do not lure her away from her duty . 不要引诱她离开职守。 5. He left home because of the lures of the life in the city. 由于受到城市生活的诱惑,他离开了家。', '副词: luringly 名词: lurer 过去式: lured 过去分词: lured 现在分词: luring 第三人称单数: lures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('systematic', '[ˌsɪstə\'mætɪk]', 'adj.有系统的；分类的；体系的；有条理的', '1. He is making a systematic study of the subject. 他在对那一科目作系统的研究。 2. The school offered a systematic course in reading. 学校提供系统的阅读课程。 3. Science means systematic knowledge possessed as a result of practice and study. 科学是由于实践和研究的结果而获得的系统知识。 4. The systematic organization of the larger teams will result in better efficiency. 构建大组制体系有利于提高效率。', '副词: systematically 异体字: systematical');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sharp', '[ʃɑːrp]', 'adj.锋利的；突然的；灵敏的；明显的；辛辣的；【音】升音阶的 adv.准时地；突然地；偏高地', '1. Cats have sharp claws. 猫有锋利的爪子。 2. There is a sharp drop in the prices. 价格出现暴跌。 3. It was very sharp of you to have noticed that. 你注意到了这一点是够机灵的。 4. Bring the object into focus if you want a sharp photograph. 要照出清晰的照片，就要把焦点对准物体。 5. We arrived at three(o\'clock) sharp. 我们在三点整到达。', '副词: sharply 比较级: sharper 最高级: sharpest 名词: sharpness 过去式: sharped 过去分词: sharped 现在分词: sharping 第三人称单数: sharps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intensive', '[ɪn\'tensɪv]', 'adj.密集的；彻底的；精细的；强调的 n.(语法)强调成份', '1. This patient requires intensive care. 该病人需要加强护理。 2. We concentrated intensive fire on the enemy. 我们集中密集的火力向敌人攻击。 3. An intensive search failed to reveal any clues. 经过彻底搜查未发现任何线索。 4. Do you have an intensive reading of English this term? 这个学期你们有英语精读课程吗？', '副词: intensively 名词: intensiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sea', '[siː]', 'n.海；海洋', '1. The moonlight shone on the calm sea. 月光映在平静的海面上。 2. The sea covers nearly three-fourths of the world\'s surface. 海洋几乎占地球表面的四分之三。 3. The sea seemed to melt into the sky at the horizon. 在水平线处，海洋似渐渐没入天际。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('documentary', '[ˌdɑːkju\'mentri]', 'n.纪录片 adj.纪实的；文件形式的', '1. The film was a documentary on politicians in Russia. 这部电影是一部关于俄罗斯政坛的纪录片。 2. We were watching a documentary about Canadian sports. 我们在观看关于加拿大体育的纪录片。 3. Her latest documentary is concerned with youth unemployment. 她最近的一部纪录片是关于青年人失业问题的。 4. The film was given a documentary style by the director. 导演以纪实的表现手法拍摄了这部影片。', '名词复数: documentaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eight', '[eɪt]', 'num.八 n.八人划船队 adj.八个的', '1. I\'m hardly functional if I don\'t get eight hours\' sleep! 我要是不睡上八个小时就无法工作。 2. You are restricted to eight liters of duty-free wine. 携带的免税酒不得超过八升。 3. There are eight forts in this section of the Great Wall. 这一段长城有八个垛口。 4. Five members voted for the proposal, eight voted against, and two abstained. 对于这项建议，五人投票赞成，八人反对，两人弃权。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pitch', '[pɪtʃ]', 'n.球场；程度；音调；推销；投掷；街头商贩摊位；沥青；树脂；松脂 v.投；颠簸；搭帐篷；定调；推销；用沥青覆盖', '1. The pitch is too small to play football on. 球场太小了, 无法踢足球。 2. Speculation has reached such a pitch that a decision will have to be made immediately. 这种胡乱猜测甚嚣尘上，已经到了必须立即解决的程度了。 3. The pitch depends on the frequency. 音调的高低是由频率决定的。 4. He has a very clever sales pitch. 他推销商品的口才很好。 5. She pitched the ball as far as she could. 她尽力把球投得远一些。', '过去式: pitched 过去分词: pitched 现在分词: pitching 第三人称单数: pitches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('joke', '[dʒoʊk]', 'n.笑话；玩笑 v.说笑话；开玩笑', '1. He closed his speech with a funny joke. 他用一则有趣的笑话结束了演讲。 2. I\'m sorry but I can\'t see the joke. 很抱歉,我看不出来有什么可笑的。 3. It is no joke. 这可不是开玩笑的事。 4. He can\'t take a joke. 他开不得玩笑。 5. He\'s someone I have an occasional chat and joke with. 我偶然跟他闲聊，一起说笑话。', '副词: jokingly 过去式: joked 过去分词: joked 现在分词: joking 第三人称单数: jokes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skeleton', '[\'skelɪtn]', 'n.骨架；纲要；骨骼；骨瘦如柴的人或动物；家丑 adj.骨骼的', '1. The block is still just a skeleton of girders. 这片建筑还只是仅有主梁的骨架。 2. The director set out the plan in skeleton form. 主任提纲挈领地说明了这一计划。 3. I\'ve written the skeleton of my report, but I have to fill in the details. 我已写出报告的梗概，但我必须补充细节。 4. The shell of a snail is its skeleton. 蜗牛的壳是它的骨骼。 5. As a part of the whole skeleton, oral maxillofacial bone loss has some association with systemic osteoporosis. 做为全身骨骼的一部分，颌骨的骨丢失一直被认为与全身骨质疏松存在关联性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commend', '[kə\'mend]', 'v.推荐；称赞；嘉奖；把 ... 托付给', '1. I should like to commend this method to you. 我想向您推荐这一方法。 2. I\'d like to commend him to my friends. 我愿意把他推荐给我的朋友们。 3. He commend them for their enthusiasm. 他称赞他们的热情。 4. The guests commend him upon his good manners 客人们称赞他有礼貌。', '形容词: commendable 副词: commendably 名词: commendableness 过去式: commended 过去分词: commended 现在分词: commending 第三人称单数: commends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('countryside', '[\'kʌntrisaɪd]', 'n.乡下；农村', '1. They lived a tranquil life in the countryside. 他们在乡下过着宁静的生活。 2. I feel healthier after a visit to the countryside. 到乡下走了一趟后我觉得身体更健康。 3. Modern agriculture is spoiling our beautiful countryside. 现代农业正在破坏我们美丽的农村。 4. These are fresh eggs from the countryside. 这是刚从农村来的新鲜鸡蛋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('format', '[\'fɔːrmæt]', 'n.版式；设计 vt.使格式化；安排', '1. The book has been styled in a modern format. 该书已按照现代版式制作。 2. It\'s the same book,but a new format. 还是那本书 3. The format of the meeting was such that every one could ask a question. 会议安排好可让每个人都能提一个问题。 4. The disk is too large to format for the specified file system. 磁盘过大,无法为指定文件系统进行格式化。', '过去式: formatted 过去分词: formatted 现在分词: formatting 第三人称单数: formats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cross', '[krɔːs]', 'v.穿过；交叉；杂交；反对；勾掉；碰见；阻挠 n.十字架；十字形；杂交动植物；苦难 adj.交叉的；相反的；生气的；杂交的', '1. It\'s very dangerous for children to cross the busy street. 对孩子们来说,穿过车来车往的街道很危险。 2. Meet me at the point where the two paths cross. 我们在那两条路的交叉点见面吧。 3. The experts in the zoo tried to cross a leopard with a lion. 动物园里的专家们试图使豹与狮子杂交。 4. He crosses me in everything. 他处处与我作对。 5. She wore a small silver cross on a chain round her neck. 她脖子上戴著项链,上面挂着个小的银制十字架。 6. There was an accident yesterday at the cross part of three roads. 昨天,在三条路的交叉路段,发生了一起事故。', '副词: crossly 名词: crosser 过去式: crossed 过去分词: crossed 现在分词: crossing 第三人称单数: crosses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('momentum', '[moʊ\'mentəm]', 'n.势头；动力；（物理）动量', '1. They began to lose momentum in the second half of the game. 在比赛的下半场，他们的势头就逐渐减弱。 2. We should continue to maintain good growth momentum. 我们应继续保持良好的增长势头。 3. I am picking up momentum every single day. 我现在每天都会获得动力。 4. The peace movement gained momentum. 和平运动获得了动力。', '名词复数: momenta');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sophisticated', '[sə\'fɪstɪkeɪtɪd]', 'adj.老练的；精密的；复杂的；久经世故的', '1. She is such a sophisticated woman that she saw through his trick at the first sight. 她是个十分老练的女人,她一眼就看穿了他的把戏。 2. As far as defense is concerned, we need to buy more sophisticated weapons. 就防御的观点来说，我们需要购买更多精密的武器。 3. The publisher\'s techniques for the promotion of his books have become increasingly sophisticated since the 1950s. 自20世纪50年代以来,出版商推销书籍的方式愈加复杂。 4. I\'d rather deal with a simple man than a sophisticated man. 我宁愿与纯朴的人打交道,不愿与世故的人交往。', '副词: sophisticatedly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('emerge', '[i\'mɜːrdʒ]', 'vi.浮现；(由某种状态)脱出；(事实)显现出来', '1. A wonderful idea emerged in my mind. 我的脑海里浮现出一个极妙的想法。 2. Man has gradually emerged from barbarism into civilization over the long history. 在悠久的历史长河中人类逐渐脱离野蛮状态而进入文明。 3. Many facts emerged as a result of the investigation. 调查结果,许多事实暴露出来。', '过去式: emerged 过去分词: emerged 现在分词: emerging 第三人称单数: emerges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inhale', '[ɪn\'heɪl]', 'v.吸入；吸气；吞咽', '1. Do you inhale when you smoke? 你抽烟时是否把烟吸入肺里？ 2. We inhale oxygen and exhale carbon dioxide. 我们吸入的是氧气，呼出的是二氧化碳。 3. He inhaled deeply. 他深深地吸了口气。 4. Follow me please, inhale! exhale! 跟我做,吸气! 呼气！', '过去式: inhaled 过去分词: inhaled 现在分词: inhaling 第三人称单数: inhales');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hard', '[hɑːrd]', 'adj.硬的；困难的；棘手的；坚强的；残酷的；用力的；液态的；严寒的；确凿的 adv.努力地；强烈地；严重地；坚定地', '1. The ground is as hard as stone after the long drought. 长期干旱之后,土地硬得就像石头一样。 2. It\'s very hard to maintain a relationship. 要维持一段关系,是很困难的。 3. It\'s very hard on parents when their children are rebellious. 对父母来说,孩子叛逆是个很棘手的问题。 4. He likes to pretend he is hard, but he is really soft underneath. 他喜欢故作坚强,但是他内心真的很脆弱。 5. Most importantly, you must work hard to catch up. 最为重要的是,你必须努力学习,迎头赶上。', '比较级: harder 最高级: hardest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obsolete', '[ˌɑːbsə\'liːt]', 'adj.已废弃的；过时的', '1. The army plans to phase out the equipment as it becomes obsolete. 军队计划淘汰这些设备，因为它们已经报废了。 2. This usage of the word is obsolete. 这个词的此类用法已经废弃了。 3. The obsolete regime is about to collapse. 那过时的政权即将崩溃。 4. You always depend on an obsolete viewpoint. 你老是信赖一个过时的观点。', '副词: obsoletely 名词: obsoleteness 过去式: obsoleted 过去分词: obsoleted 现在分词: obsoleting 第三人称单数: obsoletes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('handful', '[\'hændfʊl]', 'n.一把；少数；<非>难控制的人；棘手之事', '1. He dipped into the bag and brought out a handful of sample wheat. 他把手伸进袋里，取出一把小麦样品。 2. All the trouble is being caused by a handful of malcontents. 这些是非都是由一小撮不满分子搬弄的。 3. We invited twenty people, but only a handful of them came. 我们邀请了20 个人，但只来了寥寥数人。', '名词复数: handfuls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('term', '[tɜːrm]', 'n.学期；术语；条件；条款；期限；名词 vt.把 ... 称为', '1. Are there any exams at the end of this term? 这个学期期末有考试吗？ 2. I am not familiar with chemical terms. 我不熟悉化学术语。 3. Another firm has offered more advantageous terms than yours. 另一家公司提出的条件比你们的优惠。 4. The company has fulfilled all the terms of the agreement. 公司已经履行了协议中的所有条款。 5. He termed the play a tragedy. 他称该剧为悲剧。', '过去式: termed 过去分词: termed 现在分词: terming 第三人称单数: terms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transient', '[\'trænʃnt]', 'adj.短暂的 n.短期居留者；<电>顺变电流', '1. Her feeling of depression was transient. 她那抑郁的心情一会儿就过去了。 2. Their happiness was transient,for the war broke out soon after they got married. 他们的幸福是短暂的，因为他们婚后不久就爆发了战争。 3. We stayed at the inn as transient guests. 我们在小酒馆中只作短暂停留。 4. We are just the transients at the hotel. 我们只是旅馆里的过往旅客。', '副词: transiently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('furthermore', '[ˌfɜːrðər\'mɔːr]', 'adv.而且；此外', '1. The house is too small, and furthermore, it\'s too far from the office. 房子太小,而且离办公地点太远。 2. I don\'t want to go there, furthermore, I have no time to do so. 我不想去那里, 而且我也没时间去。 3. Furthermore, it teaches in dependence. 此外，体育还能教会人独立。 4. Furthermore, the work flow was irregular. 此外，厂里的生产流程也时断时续。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lightning', '[\'laɪtnɪŋ]', 'n.闪电；意外的幸运 adj.闪电般的；快速的', '1. The little girl is afraid of thunder and lightning. 这小女孩害怕雷声和闪电。 2. The tree was struck by lightning and splintered. 那棵树被闪电劈裂了。 3. He drove the car with lightning speed. 他以闪电般的速度开车。 4. He would shoot his water-pot into the tank with a lightning movement so as to get his supply from an uncontaminated depth. 他用闪电般的速度把水桶戳进水池里，以便能从没被污染的深处取水。', '过去式: lightninged 过去分词: lightninged 现在分词: lightning 第三人称单数: lightnings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('centigrade', '[\'sentɪɡreɪd]', 'adj.摄氏的；百分度的', '1. This thermometer is calibrated by centigrade. 这种温度计是用摄氏百分度标定的。 2. It is therefore usually expressed in percentage terms rather than in engineering units such as degrees centigrade. 因此它往往用一个百分比来表示而不是机械单位如百分度表示。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('straw', '[strɔː]', 'n.稻草；吸管；麦杆；不值钱的东西 adj.用稻草做的；麦杆色的；无价值的；像稻草人的；非正式民意测验所发现的', '1. The bird is building a nest of straw and twigs. 这只鸟在用稻草和小树枝筑巢。 2. A drowning man will catch at a straw. [谚]人快淹死时，稻草也要抓。 3. She was drinking juice through a straw. 她正在用吸管喝果汁。 4. A drowne man will catch at a straw. 溺水的人连一根麦杆也会牢牢抓住。 5. The bumblebee sizzed right under his straw hat. 大黄蜂就在他的草帽底下丝丝作声。', '形容词: strawy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adjacent', '[ə\'dʒeɪsnt]', 'adj.邻近的；毗连的；接近的', '1. The house adjacent to ours has been sold. 与我们家邻接的房子已经售出。 2. His house is adjacent to mine. 他的寓所与我的相毗连。 3. The planes landed on adjacent runways. 这些飞机在毗连的跑道上降落。 4. The island of Cuba is adjacent to Florida. 古巴岛接近佛罗里达。', '副词: adjacently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('simple', '[\'sɪmpl]', 'adj.简单的；朴素的；单纯的；笨的', '1. In each cave they constructed five simple beds. 他们在每间窑洞里做了5个简单的床。 2. As he had forgot his keys, he got into the house by the simple expedient of climbing through the window. 他由于忘了带钥匙，便以简单的应急办法从窗户爬进屋里。 3. I like my clothes to be simple but elegant. 我喜欢朴素但漂亮雅致的衣服。 4. \"A-bomb, H-bomb and nuclear-powered submarine\" 两弹一艇', '比较级: simpler 最高级: simplest 名词: simpleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inspiration', '[ˌɪnspə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.灵感；鼓舞人心(的东西)；吸气', '1. Many poets and artists have drawn their inspiration from nature. 许多诗人和艺术家从大自然中获得他们的灵感。 2. Her speeches have ever been a fount of inspiration to her audiences. 她的演说对于听众来说永远是灵感之源。 3. His wife was a constant inspiration to him. 他的妻子经常鼓励他。 4. Let\'s give mutual support and inspiration to each other. 让我们互相支持，互相鼓励。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cannon', '[\'kænən]', 'n.大炮；机关炮 v.开炮；相撞', '1. The cannon shot the town to pieces. 大炮的射击毁了这座城市。 2. Being destitute of cannon, they mounted Quaker guns in the fort. 因为没有大炮，他们只得在城堡上装设假炮。 3. The cannon thundered in the hills. 大炮在山间轰鸣。 4. Our fighter planes are all armed with cannon. 我们的战斗机都装备了机关炮。 5. put a finger into another pie', '名词复数: cannon 过去式: cannoned 过去分词: cannoned 现在分词: cannoning 第三人称单数: cannons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('illustrate', '[\'ɪləstreɪt]', 'vt.说明；（为书）作插图；图解 vi.举例说明；发亮', '1. He pointed at the diagram to illustrate his point. 他指着图表来说明他的论点。 2. In this section, I\'ll illustrate some of these differences. 在这一节,我将举例说明一些不同之处。 3. Our textbook is very well illustrated. 我们的课本插图丰富。 4. This chart is used to illustrate all the changes. 这张图片用来解释所有的变化。', '形容词: illustratable 名词: illustrator 过去式: illustrated 过去分词: illustrated 现在分词: illustrating 第三人称单数: illustrates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preferable', '[\'prefrəbl]', 'adj.更好的；更合意的', '1. To be honest, I\'ve got a preferable offer. 老实说，我有唯一更好的任务机遇。', '副词: preferably 名词: preferability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('climax', '[\'klaɪmæks]', 'n.高潮；极点；层进法；[生]顶极群落；巅峰，最高峰', '1. The music approached a climax. 乐曲接近高潮。 2. The climax of the celebration was a firework display. 庆祝会的高潮是燃放烟火。 3. The heat of summer has reached its climax. 已经是夏季最热的天气了。 4. The air war over Europe was reaching its climax. 欧洲的空战已近白热化。', '过去式: climaxed 过去分词: climaxed 现在分词: climaxing 第三人称单数: climaxes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('operator', '[\'ɑːpəreɪtər]', 'n.操作员；技工；管理者；报务员；【计】运算符', '1. I am a computer operator. 我是一名计算机操作人员。 2. Is this man a teaccher or an operator? 这个男人是老师还是名操作员? 3. The lathe is being adjusted by the operator. 这台车床正由技工在调准。 4. My father is a private operator in civil aviation. 我父亲是私营民航的管理者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('juvenile', '[\'dʒuːvənl]', 'adj.青少年的；幼稚的 n.青少年；青少年读物；幼雏；扮演少年的演员', '1. I\'m afraid he\'ll ultimately become a juvenile delinquent. 我恐怕他最终会成为一名青少年罪犯。 2. They are holding a forum on juvenile delinquency. 他们正举行一个有关青少年犯罪的讨论会。 3. He is an expert in juvenile delinquency. 他是研究青少年犯罪的专家。 4. He wrote down to the juvenile readers. 他为青少年读者写浅显的作品。 5. They are holding a forum on juvenile delinquency. 他们正举行一个有关青少年犯罪的讨论会。', '副词: juvenilely 名词: juvenileness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('imaginary', '[ɪ\'mædʒɪneri]', 'adj.想象的；虚构的', '1. We play out an imaginary confrontation in our mind. 我们的脑海中浮现出一种想象的冲突。 2. The boy\'s fears were only imaginary. 这小孩的恐惧只是一种想象。 3. People still have a general fear for the imaginary infernal powers. 人们对于虚构的地狱中的鬼神仍具有一种普遍的恐惧。 4. All the characters in this book are imaginary. 这本书中的人物都是虚构的。', '副词: imaginarily 名词: imaginariness 名词复数: imaginaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('agent', '[\'eɪdʒənt]', 'n.代理人；代理商；药剂；特工人员', '1. I have been instructed by my agent that you still owe me 100 pounds. 我的代理人通知我，你还欠我100磅。 2. The agent priced the house at the right level for the market. 代理商按市场价格给这所房子定了价。 3. This is a chemical agent that destroys plants or inhibits their growth. 这是一种能除草或抑制其生长的化学药剂。 4. The officer inspired the secret agent to murder the president . 这个军官鼓动这个特工人员去谋杀总统。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hero', '[\'hɪroʊ]', 'n.英雄 n.男主角；男主人公', '1. The hero smote the giant with his sword. 英雄用剑猛劈巨人。 2. He is the hero of an old legend. 他是一个古老传说中的英雄。 3. They say the hero is played by Tom Cruise. 据说男主角是汤姆·克鲁斯。 4. Who is going to play to the hero of the play? 谁来演与男主角相配的女主角?', '名词复数: heroes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('solo', '[\'soʊloʊ]', 'n.独奏；独唱 adj.单独的 adv.单独地 v.单独表演；[空]放单飞(飞行员一个人开飞机,无教练陪同)', '1. The first piece is a piano solo by Berio. 第一个节目是贝里奥的钢琴独奏。 2. The concert began with piano solo. 音乐会以一首钢琴独奏开始。 3. He has been asked to sing a solo at the concert. 他已被邀请在演奏会上表演独唱。 4. The student essayed his first solo flight. 该学员尝试作首次单独飞行。 5. His landing was awkward,but it was only the second time he\'d flown solo. 他的着陆技术很不熟练,但这只是他第二次单飞。', '名词复数: solos 过去式: soloed 过去分词: soloed 现在分词: soloing 第三人称单数: solos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('difficulty', '[\'dɪfɪkəlti]', 'n.困难；争议；麻烦', '1. He experienced great difficulty in getting a visa to leave the country. 他申请出国签证经历了很大的困难。 2. He faced the difficulty with courage. 他勇敢地面对困难。 3. Have you any concrete thoughts on how to deal with this difficulty? 处理这种困难你有什么具体的想法？ 4. A difficulty has cropped up at work. 工作中突然出现困难。', '名词复数: difficulties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('defeat', '[dɪ\'fiːt]', 'n.挫败；败北 vt.战胜；击败；使...不能实现', '1. He was depressed by his defeat. 失败让他沮丧。 2. This defeat was a powerful blow to the enemy. 这次失败是对敌人的有力的打击。 3. The news of army\'s defeat cast a gloom over the town. 军队败北的消息给小城蒙上了一层忧郁。 4. They are still wailing over their defeat. 他们仍在为比赛失利而悲叹。 5. It was a sound strategy to defeat the enemy. 那是战胜敌人的良策。', '名词: defeater 过去式: defeated 过去分词: defeated 现在分词: defeating 第三人称单数: defeats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jeans', '[dʒiːnz]', 'n.牛仔裤', '1. Every other girl except me is wearing jeans. 除了我以外，其他姑娘都穿著牛仔裤。 2. He wears an oily old pair of jeans. 他穿着一条沾满油污的旧牛仔裤。 3. Both my sister and I like to wear jeans. 我姐姐和我都喜欢穿牛仔裤。 4. The jeans will shrink in the wash. 那些牛仔裤洗过以后会缩水。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enter', '[\'entər]', 'v.进入 【计算机】送入', '1. Please do not enter before knocking on the door. 进来前请先敲门。 2. He has no choice but enter that college. 他不得不进入那所大学读书。 3. He showed me how to enter data into the computer. 他告诉我如何将数据输入电脑。', '形容词: enterable 过去式: entered 过去分词: entered 现在分词: entering 第三人称单数: enters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refine', '[rɪ\'faɪn]', 'v.精炼；改进；使更文雅', '1. The oil will be refined. 这些石油将被精炼。 2. Their daily work is to refine crude oil. 他们每天的工作是精炼原油。 3. Sugar, oil and metals are refined before use. 糖, 油和金属在使用前须先提炼。 4. We shall have to refine on our methods of advertising. 我们得进一步改进做广告的方法。', '名词: refiner 过去式: refined 过去分词: refined 现在分词: refining 第三人称单数: refines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('amplifier', '[\'æmplɪfaɪər]', 'n.放大器；扩音机', '1. Output from the inverting oscillator amplifier. 内部反向振荡放大器的输出。 2. A quad amplifier contains four identical circuit units. 一台四元组放大器包含四个恒等电路单元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('motion', '[\'moʊʃn]', 'n.移动；动作；打手势；示意；提议；大便 v.示意；运动；向 ... 打手势', '1. The object is no longer in motion. 该物体已不处於运动状态. 2. Parts of the film were shown again in slow motion. 影片的一些部分以慢动作重放。 3. He made a motion with his hand to make me sit down. 他招手示意要我坐下。 4. His motion was rejected. 他的提议遭到了拒绝。 5. He opened the door and motioned me to come in. 他打开了门，招手让我进去。', '过去式: motioned 过去分词: motioned 现在分词: motioning 第三人称单数: motions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('name', '[neɪm]', 'n.名称；姓名；名义；名誉；名人 v.命名；取名；说出( ... 的名字) adj.著名的', '1. The committee\'s name has been acronymed NACA. 该委员会的名称被缩合成NACA。 2. Rubella is just another name for German measles. 风疹只是德国麻疹的另一个名称。 3. She signed the poem with her real name. 她在诗后署上了自己的真实姓名。 4. He refused to disclose his name and address. 他拒绝透露自己的姓名和地址。 5. You can name the bookmark at design time. 您可以在设计时命名书签。', '形容词: namable 名词: namer 过去式: named 过去分词: named 现在分词: naming 第三人称单数: names');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contemporary', '[kən\'tempəreri]', 'adj.同时代的；当代的 n.同时代的人；同龄人', '1. Marlowe was contemporary with Shakespeare. 马洛与莎士比亚是同时代的。 2. He had devoted his whole life to the study of contemporary art. 他把他的一生都献给了当代艺术研究。 3. Thackeray is a contemporary of Dickens. 萨克莱跟狄更斯是同时期的人。 4. She and I were contemporaries at college. 她和我在学院里是同学。', '副词: contemporarily 名词复数: contemporaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('maid', '[meɪd]', 'n.【C】女仆；侍女 n.【古】未婚女子', '1. Her maid helped her to dress up for the party. 她的女仆帮助她穿上参加晚会的礼服。 2. I\'ll send the maid round to carry it to your house. 我将派女仆把它送到你家去。 3. The maid lowered her chin and simpered. 那位侍女压低下额傻笑着。 4. They have two servants, a cook and a maid. 他们有两个仆人，一个厨子和一个侍女。 5. Maids want nothing but husbands, and when they have them, they want everything. 待嫁女子除了丈夫以外什么都不想要,可是,当她们有了丈夫之后,什么都想要了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pretext', '[\'priːtekst]', 'n.借口 v.以…为借口', '1. He stayed away under the pretext of ill health. 他以身体不佳为借口而避开了。 2. He refused to see them on one pretext or another. 他以种种借口拒绝见他们。', '过去式: pretexted 过去分词: pretexted 现在分词: pretexting 第三人称单数: pretexts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('childhood', '[\'tʃaɪldhʊd]', 'n.童年；幼年', '1. I have only misty memories of my early childhood. 我对自己的童年只剩一些模糊的记忆。 2. He had a lively remembrance of his childhood. 他对他的童年生活记忆犹新。 3. Childhood is a period of rapid growth. 幼年是生长迅速的时期。 4. I had known him from his childhood. 我从他幼年起就认识他。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exception', '[ɪk\'sepʃn]', 'n.例外；不合规则；反对；[律]异议', '1. There is always an exception to any rule. 任何规律总有例外。 2. All students without exception must take the English examination. 所有的学生毫无例外，都必须参加英语考试。 3. The spelling of this word is an interesting exception to the rule. 这个词的拼写很有趣,是本规则的例外。 4. He took great exception to what I said. 他极力反对我的话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('underneath', '[ˌʌndər\'niːθ]', 'adv.在下面 n.下部；底部 prep.在 ... 下面', '1. She was wearing a woolen coat, with a cotton blouse underneath. 她外面穿了一件毛外套，里面穿一件棉布衬衫。 2. Put a bowl underneath to catch the overflow. 把盆放在下面接住溢出物。 3. The glacier is constantly shifting underneath. 冰川在下面持续的移动。 4. The underneath part felt damp. 底层很潮湿。 5. She found a lot of dust underneath the carpet. 她发觉地毯下面有许多尘土.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('troop', '[truːp]', 'n.群；组；军队；大量 vi.群集；结队；成群前行', '1. There is a troop of monkeys in the woods. 林子中有一群猴子。 2. The enemy made a thrust against our troop. 敌人向我军发动了袭击。 3. The troop made good their retreat from the occupied city. 部队从沦陷的城市安全撤出。 4. He came out with a troop of followers. 他带着一大群随从走出来。 5. We trooped into the meeting. 我们一起走进会场。', '过去式: trooped 过去分词: trooped 现在分词: trooping 第三人称单数: troops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('constitution', '[ˌkɒnstə\'tjuːʃən]', 'n.宪法；组织；体质；构成，组成，构造', '1. The President swore to uphold the constitution. 总统宣誓维护宪法。 2. The country\'s constitution embodies the ideals of freedom and equality. 这个国家的宪法体现了自由和平等的理想。 3. The constitution of a primitive society is not necessarily simple. 原始社会的结构并不一定就是简单的。 4. Hunger and disease had weakened his constitution. 他饥饿与疾病交加，体质已削弱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suppress', '[sə\'pres]', 'vt.镇压；隐瞒；压制；止住；禁止', '1. The revolt was suppressed in a matter of hours. 叛乱在几小时之内就镇压下去了。 2. All these movements were suppressed by the warlord government. 所有这些运动都受到军阀政府的镇压。 3. A common person would not suppress his real name. 一个平常人是不会隐瞒他的真实姓名的。 4. He couldn\'t suppress his anger. 他简直怒不可遏。', '形容词: suppressible 名词: suppressant 过去式: suppressed 过去分词: suppressed 现在分词: suppressing 第三人称单数: suppresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tractor', '[\'træktər]', 'n.【C】拖拉机；牵引车', '1. The tractor pulls well. 这台拖拉机拉力大。 2. The tractor had been damaged by rough usage. 这辆拖拉机因使用不经心而损坏了。 3. A tractor towed the car to the repair factory. 一辆牵引车将汽车拖去修理厂。 4. The tractor has make deep furrow in the loose sand. 曳引机在松软的沙土上留下了深深的车辙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('certain', '[\'sɜːrtn]', 'adj.确定的；肯定的；某事；某人；某种；（与人名连用；表示不认识此人）一位叫...；特定的；轻微的；微小的 pron.某些；某几个', '1. It\'s certain that every effect must have a cause. 无疑，每个结果必定有其原因。 2. I can tell you for certain that I am always honest. 我可以肯定地告诉你, 我一向是老实的。 3. Certain things are still open to discussion. 有些事还需要商量。 4. A certain man will visit you tomorrow. 明天某人将探访你。 5. Certain of those present had had too much to drink. 有些出席的人喝得太多了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compel', '[kəm\'pel]', 'v.强迫；迫使；使不得已', '1. Nothing can compel me to do such a thing. 没有什么可以强迫我做这件事。 2. I was compelled to do so by absolute necessity. 我因绝对的需要,被迫这样做的。 3. The heavy rain compelled us to stay indoors. 大雨迫使我们呆在户内。 4. Duty compelled the soldiers to volunteer for the mission. 责任驱使军人必须志愿加入此任务', '形容词: compellable 副词: compellably 名词: compeller 过去式: compelled 过去分词: compelled 现在分词: compelling 第三人称单数: compels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shall', '[ʃəl]', 'aux.将要；应该；一定；表示提供建议', '1. Shall we all go to the film tonight? 我们今晚都去看电影吗? 2. Everything shall be in good order. 一切都应该井然有序。 3. World peace is a cause we shall all work for. 争取世界和平是一项我们都应该为之而努力的事业。 4. I shall follow all your instructions. 我一定照您的指示去做。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dew', '[duː]', 'n.露水', '1. Dew dripped from the trees. 露水从树上滴下来。 2. The grass was sprinkled with dew. 草上沾满了露珠。 3. The dew on the grass drizzled my shoes. 草上的露水打湿了我的鞋。', '过去式: dewed 过去分词: dewed 现在分词: dewing 第三人称单数: dews');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forthcoming', '[ˌfɔːrθ\'kʌmɪŋ]', 'adj.即将到来的；现成的；乐意帮助的', '1. He was exhilarateed by the thought of his forthcoming trip. 他想到即将到来的旅行，就兴高采烈。 2. Do you have a list of forthcoming books? 你有即将问世书本的目录吗? 3. The money we asked for was not forthcoming. 我们要的钱尚未得到。 4. She\'s never very forthcoming about her plans. 她一直不很愿意说出自己的计划。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('change', '[tʃeɪndʒ]', 'n.变化；零钱 v.改变', '1. His perception of the change came in a flash. 他在一瞬间察觉到了这一变化。 2. The change in the weather has mucked up our sports timetable. 天气的变化打乱了我们运动比赛的日程。 3. This is a tremendous change unparalleled in the history of China and of the world. 这是一个绝大的变化，这是自有世界历史和中国历史以来无可比拟的大变化。 4. The little boy reached in his pocket and pulled out some change. 小男孩把手伸进口袋，掏出了一些零钱。 5. Please telephone me if you are to change the day of our meeting. 如果你不得不改变我们会晤的日期，请给我打个电话。', '过去式: changed 过去分词: changed 现在分词: changing 第三人称单数: changes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('moment', '[\'moʊmənt]', 'n.片刻；瞬间；力矩；非常重要的时机；准确时刻', '1. I\'ll be back in a moment. 我一会儿就回来。 2. Would you take a seat for a moment? 请你稍坐片刻好吗? 3. He thought for a moment and then spoke. 他想了片刻，然後说。 4. Love is a moment that lasts forever. 爱的瞬间就是永恒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dye', '[daɪ]', 'n.染料；染色 v.染；染色', '1. The dye works its way in. 染料渗透进去了。 2. A good dye will not fade. 染得好的颜色不会褪色。 3. The dye doesn\'t take in cold water. 那种染料在冷水中不起作用。 4. After mercerizing, the goods are sent to the dye house or colour shop. 绦光后的产品送往染色车间或印花车间。 5. They used only natural pigments to dye the wool. 他们只用天然颜料染毛织品。', '名词: dyer 过去式: dyed 过去分词: dyed 现在分词: dyeing 第三人称单数: dyes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abnormal', '[æb\'nɔːrml]', 'adj.反常的；不正常的；变态的 n.不正常的人', '1. We were very surprised at his abnormal behavior. 我们对他的反常行为感到非常吃惊。 2. At one time, she is fine, but at another, she is abnormal. 有时候，她表现得很好，有时候又失常。 3. He is mentally abnormal. 他精神不正常。 4. It\'s abnormal for the boy to eat so much. 这个孩子吃这么多是不正常的。 5. This is an abnormal phenomenon and we must work seriously to eradicate it. 这是一种很不正常的现象，一定要认真扭转。', '副词: abnormally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('destroy', '[dɪ\'strɔɪ]', 'v.破坏；杀死；消灭；摧毁', '1. If the tree falls that way, it will destroy the house. 这棵树向那边倒下就会把那所房子压坏。 2. We want to nurture the new project, not destroy it. 我们要支持这个新工程，不要破坏它。 3. The new law operates to destroy our advantages. 这项新法律损害我们的利益。 4. He had to destroy the injured animal. 他只好杀死那个受伤的动物。', '过去式: destroyed 过去分词: destroyed 现在分词: destroying 第三人称单数: destroys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skillful', '[\'skɪlfəl]', 'adj.熟练的；灵巧的', '1. His skillful manipulation vivified this puppet. 他熟练的操作让木偶栩栩如生。 2. He is a skillful English-speaking professor. 他是位英语讲得很熟练的教授。 3. Her skillful fingers spun the wool out to a fine thread. 她那灵巧的手指把羊毛纺织成了细线。 4. With a skillful movement he rounded the small fishing-boat. 他以灵巧的动作使小渔船调过头来。', '副词: skillfully 名词: skillfulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('numerous', '[\'nuːmərəs]', 'adj.为数众多的；许多', '1. The Earth is only one of the numerous planets in the universe. 地球只是宇宙中众多星球中的一个。 2. Those birds have become more numerous lately. 近来那种鸟变得越来越多了。 3. Numerous interruptions have prevented me from finishing my work. 我屡遭搅扰以致工作未能完成。 4. He appeared, surrounded by his numerous progeny. 他出现时，子女前呼后拥不计其数。', '副词: numerously 名词: numerousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('regime', '[reɪ\'ʒiːm]', 'n.政体；政权；制度 n.养生法(=regimen)', '1. The people are held down by a vicious and repressive military regime. 人民受着凶恶而专制的军事政权的压迫。 2. The old capitalist regime is on its last legs. 旧的资本主义制度即将灭亡。 3. The regime has been propped up by foreign aid. 该政权是靠外国援助维持着的。 4. The overthrow of the regime was followed by a period of anarchy. 那政权被推翻以後，有一段时期是无政府状态。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wage', '[weɪdʒ]', 'n.工资；报酬 v.开展；从事；进行(战争、运动)', '1. A postman\'s wages are 180 per week. 邮递员的工资为每周180英镑。 2. In our family both my husband and I are wage earners. 在我们家里，丈夫和我都挣工资。 3. In order to circumvent the straitjacket of national wage rates, employers in many cities offer non-pecuniary rewards to their workers. 为了避免全国工资率的约束，许多城市的雇主不以金钱的形式付给工人报酬。 4. I am saying that in most cases, if you were to look at a pure dollar-per-hour \"wage,\" you would find that many bloggers work rather inexpensively. 而是说大部分情况下，如果你在看一份一小时只有一美元报酬的工作，那么你会发现很多博客在廉价工作。 5. The government is waging a campaign against sex discrimination in industry. 政府正在展开反对工业界性别歧视的运动。', '过去式: waged 过去分词: waged 现在分词: waging 第三人称单数: wages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('block', '[blɑːk]', 'n.街区；木块；石块；大楼；一组；阻塞(物)；障碍(物) v.阻塞', '1. Walk two blocks down the street and go past the city hall. 顺这条街走两个街区，过市政厅。 2. The doctors succeeded in confining the contagious disease within the block. 医生们成功地将这个传染病控制在这一街区的范围内。 3. The floor was made of wooden blocks. 地板是用木块拼成的。 4. The blocks should be laid on a bed of concrete. 石块应该固定在混凝土基座上。', '名词: blocker 过去式: blocked 过去分词: blocked 现在分词: blocking 第三人称单数: blocks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alert', '[ə\'lɜːrt]', 'adj.警觉的；灵敏的 vt.使意识到；警惕 n.警戒；警报', '1. The alert leopard went up to a deer quietly. 警觉的豹子静悄悄地走近一只鹿。 2. Although he\'s over eighty his mind is still remarkably alert. 他虽已年过八十，但头脑仍然十分机敏。 3. I must alert him to the need to solve the problem. 我必须使他认识到解决这问题的必要性。 4. But we must remain on the alert. 但是我们现在仍然要保持警惕。 5. Troops are on the alert against any possible aggression. 军队戒备着可能的来犯。', '过去式: alerted 过去分词: alerted 现在分词: alerting 第三人称单数: alerts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('charge', '[tʃɑːrdʒ]', 'n.责任；电荷；指控；费用；照顾 vi.要价；充电；向前冲，冲锋；记在账上 vt.控诉；赊帐；给…充电；委以重任；归罪于；装填（炸药等）', '1. As group leader, you should take charge. 你身为组长, 应当负起责任来。 2. He was arrested on a charge of armed robbery. 他被指控犯武装抢劫罪而遭逮捕。 3. Rub the leather and the rubber will produce the charge. 摩擦皮毛和橡胶会产生电荷。 4. He was arrested on a charge of armed robbery. 他被指控犯武装抢劫罪而遭逮捕。 5. How much do you charge per unit? 你们每件要价多少呢？ 6. The suspect was charged with murdering his wife. 嫌疑犯被控诉为谋杀他的妻子。', '过去式: charged 过去分词: charged 现在分词: charging 第三人称单数: charges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heir', '[er]', 'n.继承人', '1. Tilda seems to be his only heir. 迪儿特似乎是他唯一的继承人。 2. The young heir played away the whole of the estate. 那个年轻的继承人把全部遗产都赌输了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('this', '[ðɪs]', 'pron.这；这个 adj.这个 adv.这样；这么', '1. This is, in part, my own mistake. 在某种程度上来说,这是我自己的错。 2. Now don\'t laugh when you hear this. 听了这个你不要笑。 3. It\'s about this high. 大约有这样高。 4. I didn\'t think we\'d get this far. 我未曾想到我们会走得这么远。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('offspring', '[\'ɔːfsprɪŋ]', 'n.后代；子孙；产物', '1. His offspring are diligent and intelligent. 他的后代既勤奋又聪明。 2. The hybrid offspring of a zebra and a horse. 杂交斑马斑马与马杂交的后代 3. His offspring inherit the estate. 他的孩子继承了房地产。 4. How do parents pass genes on to their offspring? 父母是怎样把基因遗传给自己的子女的？', '名词复数: offspring');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('choke', '[tʃoʊk]', 'vi.窒息；阻塞；说不出话 vt.使窒息；阻塞；抑制；使说不出话 n.窒息；阻塞；阻风门', '1. She looked like she was going to choke. 她看起来仿佛都要窒息了。 2. She found it hard to choke down her anger. 她感到难以压下心中的怒火。 3. She choked with emotion. 她激动得说不出话来。 4. Very small toys can choke a baby. 很小的玩具可使婴儿窒息。 5. Very small toys can choke a baby. 很小的玩具可使婴儿窒息。', '过去式: choked 过去分词: choked 现在分词: choking 第三人称单数: chokes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scramble', '[\'skræmbl]', 'n.混乱；攀爬；争夺 v.攀爬；混杂；争抢；紧急起飞；杂乱地生长', '1. A table was pushed over in the scramble. 在混乱中一张桌子被推翻了。 2. It\'s quite a scramble to get to the top of the hill! 要往上爬很长一段路才能到达山顶呢！ 3. He broke his leg in his scramble down the wall. 他爬墙摔断了腿。 4. There was a scramble for the best seats. 大家都在抢最好的座位。 5. How can you scramble up such a steep hillside? 你怎么能爬上这么陡峭的山坡?', '过去式: scrambled 过去分词: scrambled 现在分词: scrambling 第三人称单数: scrambles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('small', '[smɔːl]', 'adj.小的；年幼的；少的；不重要的；小气的 adv.小地；小块地；小声地 n.狭小部分；(pl.)零星物品；(pl.)小件衣服', '1. This coat is too small for me. 这件上衣对我来说太小了。 2. I need to buy a small transistor radio. 我需要买一台小的半导体收音机。 3. The penalty clause was hidden in the small print. 惩罚条款印在不起眼的小号字体部分。 4. She was born in Dominica in the Caribbean and came to Britain as a small child. 她出生在加勒比海的多米尼加共和国，年幼时来到英国。 5. He writes so small I can\'t read it. 他字写得太小,我看不清。 6. He felt a sharp pain in the small of his back. 他感觉后腰一阵剧痛。', '形容词: smallish 比较级: smaller 最高级: smallest 名词: smallness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('palm', '[pɑːm]', 'n.手掌；棕榈 vt.把 ... 藏于掌中；诓骗某人', '1. He rubbed his palm across his forehead. 他用手掌揉了揉前额。 2. He knew the passage like the palm of his hand. 他对这条航线了如指掌。 3. He wrote the phone number on his palm. 他把电话号码写在手掌上。 4. Growing along the river are tall palm trees. 沿着这条河生长的是高大的棕树。 5. The goalkeeper just managed to palm the ball over the crossbar. 守门员用手掌将球托出了球门的横木。', '名词: palmful 过去式: palmed 过去分词: palmed 现在分词: palming 第三人称单数: palms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dollar', '[\'dɑːlər]', 'n.美元', '1. The Japanese yen rebounded against the dollar. 日元与美元的比价回升了。 2. Can you lend me five dollars? 你能借给我五美元吗？ 3. The pound stayed firm against dollar in London but fell a little in New York. 在伦敦英镑对美元仍坚挺，但在纽约却跌了一点儿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conquer', '[\'kɑːŋkər]', 'vt.征服；克服；战胜 vi.得胜', '1. Conquer the desire, or they will conquer you. 你不战胜欲念，欲念就会征服你。 2. If we want light, we must conquer darkness. 我们要光明，就得征服黑暗。 3. No difficulties can shake their resolve to conquer nature. 环境再艰苦也动摇不了他们征服自然的决心。 4. The only way to conquer a fear is to face it. 克服恐惧的唯一方法是正视恐惧。 5. We have no choice but to conquer. 我们别无选择，只有获胜。', '形容词: conquerable 名词: conqueror 过去式: conquered 过去分词: conquered 现在分词: conquering 第三人称单数: conquers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comparative', '[kəm\'pærətɪv]', 'adj.比较的；相当的 n.比较级', '1. He majored in comparative literature. 他的专业是比较文学。 2. To illustrate my point I have done a comparative analysis. 为说明我的观点，我做了对比分析。 3. The expedition was a comparative success. 那次探险相当成功。 4. He is a comparative stranger in our impression. 在我们的印象中他是个相当陌生的人。 5. \"Worse\" is the comparative of \"bad\". \"worse\"是\"bad\"的比较级。', '副词: comparatively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('classify', '[\'klæsɪfaɪ]', 'vt.分类；归类', '1. The books in the library are classified by subject. 图书馆的书是按科目分类的。 2. We can classify these subjects under three headings. 我们可以将这些题目加以分类成三个主题。 3. Would you classify her novels as serious literature or other? 你认为她的小说属于文学类，还是其它类? 4. It is entirly proper to classify Kant as a transcendental idealist. 把康德化归类为先验的唯心主义者是完全正确的。', '形容词: classifiable 过去式: classified 过去分词: classified 现在分词: classifying 第三人称单数: classifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resultant', '[rɪ\'zʌltənt]', 'adj.作为结果的；合成的 n.结果；产物；[数学] 合矢量；结式', '1. The resultant human form now ran on electromagnetic energy. 合成的人类形体现在运作着电磁能量。 2. All elements are radiating in phase, and the resultant wave front is perpendicular to the axis of the element array. 所有单元发射相位一致，合成的波前垂直于单元阵列轴线。 3. This snap-in allows you to browse Resultant Set of Policy data. 此管理单元允许您浏览策略数据的结果集。 4. He is arrested for drunkenness and the resultant publicity ruined his career. 他因酗酒被捕，结果这一坏名声毁了他的前程。', '副词: resultantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('any', '[\'eni]', 'adj.任何的 adv.稍微；丝毫 pron.任何', '1. I can\'t stay any longer. 我一刻也不能再呆下去了。 2. I can\'t see things getting any better 我看不出事情有丝毫好转', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('embassy', '[\'embəsi]', 'n.大使馆；大使全体人员', '1. The terrorists have occupied the Embassy. 恐怖分子占领了大使馆。 2. A crowd had already collected outside the embassy gates. 使馆大门外已经聚集了一群人。 3. Two attaches at the embassy were expelled from the country. 大使馆的两名随员已驱逐出境。 4. The consulate was upgraded to embassy status. 该领事馆已升格为大使馆。', '名词复数: embassies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('common', '[\'kɑːmən]', 'adj.常见的；共同的；普通的；平常的；平凡的；粗俗的 n.公地；平民；普通；公园', '1. Windmills are a common sight in Holland. 风车是荷兰常见的景色。 2. We have common topics to talk about. 我们有共同的话题可谈。 3. Common interests bind us together. 共同的利益使我们结合在一起。 4. Smith is a common surname. 史密斯是个很普通的姓。 5. We went for a walk on the common. 我们在公地上散步。', '副词: commonly 比较级: commoner 最高级: commonest 名词: commonness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('town', '[taʊn]', 'n.城市；城镇；（某一城镇的）居民；商业区', '1. The town was invaded by reporters. 这个城市涌进了大批记者。 2. It\'s a great convenience to live in town. 住在城市里有很大的方便。 3. Would you rather live in a town, or in the country? 你愿意住在城市还是乡下？ 4. The town has been designated a development area. 该城市已被定为开发区。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mechanical', '[mə\'kænɪkl]', 'adj.机械的；力学的；呆板的', '1. The new car had to be withdrawn from the market because of a mechanical defect. 那种新汽车因有机械缺陷只好撤出市场。 2. They were using a mechanical shovel to clear up the streets. 他们用机械铲土机清理街道。 3. The inhomogeneity of the physical and mechanical characteristics can be considered in these models. 在这些模型中考虑了土的物理和力学的非线性特性。 4. Blinking is a mechanical action of the eyelids. 眨眼是眼睑的无意识动作。', '副词: mechanically 名词: mechanicalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('constitute', '[\'kɑːnstətuːt]', 'vt.构成；组成；任命；建立；制定', '1. Twelve months constitute one year. 十二个月构成一年。 2. Correct grammar and sentence structure do not in themselves constitute good writing. 正确的语法和句子结构本身并不能构成一篇好文章。 3. The committee is constituted of members of all three parties. 委员会由所有三个政党的成员组成。 4. He was constituted representative of the party. 他被任命为该党的代表。', '名词: constituter 过去式: constituted 过去分词: constituted 现在分词: constituting 第三人称单数: constitutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bunch', '[bʌntʃ]', 'n.串；束；一群；捆 n.突出物；凸起 vt.使成一束(或一群等) vi.隆起；成束成群', '1. I bought a bunch of grapes. 我买了一串葡萄。 2. He gave a bunch of flowers to his girlfriend. 他送给女友一束花。 3. He goes round with a bunch of thugs. 他经常和一帮流氓厮混。 4. Can you make these flowers a bunch? 请你把这些花系成捆行吗? 5. Be sure not to bunch the flowers up tightly. 务必不要把花束捆得太紧。 6. His arm muscles bunch out when he lift the stone lion. 他举起石狮时臂上的肌肉一块一块隆起。', '形容词: bunchy 名词: bunchiness 过去式: bunched 过去分词: bunched 现在分词: bunching 第三人称单数: bunches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soluble', '[\'sɑːljəbl]', 'adj.可溶解的；可解决的', '1. Soluble metallic hydroxides are bases that are alkalies. 可溶解的金属氢氧化合物都是碱。 2. A subsequent wet depithing serves to remove soluble and strongly adhering pith. 后续的除髓工序可以继续除去可溶解的和粘附牢固的蔗髓。', '副词: solubly 名词: solubleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crash', '[kræʃ]', 'v.撞击；坠毁；发出巨响；崩溃；破产；<俚>宿夜 n.轰隆声；猛撞；崩溃；暴跌；垮台；粗布 adj.速成的', '1. He crashed his car into a wall. 他的汽车撞到了墙上。 2. The rocks crashed down onto the car. 岩石轰隆一声砸在汽车上。 3. She was frightened that the plane would crash. 她害怕飞机会坠毁。 4. The plane crashed (into the mountain). 飞机撞毁(在山上)了。 5. The building fell with a crash as loud as thunder. 建筑物轰隆一声倒塌了，声如雷鸣。 6. The project was launched on a crash basis. 此计划作为最优先项目而付诸实施。', '名词: crasher 过去式: crashed 过去分词: crashed 现在分词: crashing 第三人称单数: crashes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('agony', '[\'æɡəni]', 'n.极度的痛苦；挣扎', '1. It was great agony to watch him passing away. 看着他死去是极大的痛苦。 2. The agony of that moment was terrific. 那一刹那的痛苦是可怕的。 3. He was in an agony of remorse. 他处于悔恨的海洋中。 4. Rescue the jobber girl who struggles in agony. 救救痛苦中挣扎的打工妹。', '名词复数: agonies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('other', '[\'ʌðər]', 'adj.其他的；另外的；另一个；另一边 pron.其他(人或物) n.其他人(或事) adv.以其他方式', '1. They discussed the weather and other topics. 他们讨论了气候和其他的话题。 2. He overtook the other runners on the last lap. 他在最后一圈时超过了其他的赛跑选手。 3. Problems always lead to other problems. 有些问题总是连带着另外的问题。 4. My other sister is a doctor. 我的另一个妹妹是医生。 5. The children are always bickering about something or other. 孩子们有事没事总是在争吵。 6. After her departure the others resumed the discussion. 她走之后，其余的人继续讨论 7. You can\'t get there other than by swimming. 你只能靠游泳游到那边去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sociology', '[ˌsoʊsi\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.社会学；<生>群落生态学', '1. Economics and sociology are social sciences. 经济学和社会学都属于社会科学。 2. A few years ago, sociology is the most popular subject for undergraduate. 几年之前，社会学是大学本科生最欢迎的课程。', '形容词: sociologic 副词: sociologically 名词: sociologist');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dirty', '[\'dɜːrti]', 'adj.脏的；肮脏的；下流的；卑鄙的；腐败的；不正当的 v.弄脏；玷污', '1. The clothes on the floor are dirty. 地板上的那些衣物是脏的. 2. The tourist complained that the room was too dirty. 游客抱怨说房间太脏了。 3. The dirty pub is a beastly place. 那个肮脏的小酒馆是一个叫人恶心的地方。 4. They sat drinking and telling dirty stories. 他们坐在那里，边喝酒边讲下流故事。 5. You\'ll dirty your hand if you play in the dirt. 如果你去玩泥巴，手会弄脏。', '副词: dirtily 比较级: dirtier 最高级: dirtiest 名词: dirtiness 过去式: dirtied 过去分词: dirtied 现在分词: dirtying 第三人称单数: dirties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('parachute', '[\'pærəʃuːt]', 'n.降落伞；缓降物；[动]翅膜 v.跳伞；用降落伞空投', '1. The parachute puffed all around. 降落伞噗地张开了。 2. Supplies were dropped by parachute. 补给品由降落伞空投。 3. My parachute eased me groundward. 降落伞载着我徐徐下落。 4. Our first parachute jump was an exhilarating experience. 我们第一次跳伞感到兴奋莫名。 5. The pilot was able to parachute to safety. 飞行员得以安全跳伞。', '形容词: parachutic 名词: parachutist 过去式: parachuted 过去分词: parachuted 现在分词: parachuting 第三人称单数: parachutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('twice', '[twaɪs]', 'adv.两倍；两次', '1. I am more than twice as old as he. 我的年龄是他的两倍还不止。 2. The length of the table is twice its breadth. 桌子的长度是它的宽度的两倍。 3. I\'ve seen this film twice. 这部影片我已经看过两次了。 4. We should brush our teeth at least twice a day. 我们每天应该至少刷两次牙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('studio', '[\'stuːdioʊ]', 'n.画室；工作室；播音室；制片厂；摄影场', '1. Upstairs he has a studio where he paints a little. 他在楼上有一个画室，有时在那里作一点画。 2. I was talking to her in the studio. 我那时正在工作室跟它谈话。 3. The studio is being wired for sound. 这个播音室正在安装音响设备用的电线。 4. She must be in the television studio at the moment. 她现在一定在电视演播室。', '名词复数: studios');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cylinder', '[\'sɪlɪndər]', 'n.圆筒；汽缸；圆柱体', '1. The cylinder is a crucial part of the washing machine. 滚筒是洗衣机必不可少的部分。 2. She handed over a small metal cylinder. 她递过来一个小的金属圆筒。 3. The engine is misfiring badly on one cylinder. 发动机有一个汽缸严重失灵。 4. The accident didn\'t do much damage to the cylinder. 在意外事故中，汽缸没有受到重大损坏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('copy', '[\'kɑːpi]', 'n.复制品；抄本；副本；一册；一份 v.复制；抄写；抄袭', '1. The painting is a copy of one in the museum. 这幅画是博物馆中的一幅画的复制品。 2. He asked his secretary to make a copy of the document. 他叫秘书把文件复制一份。 3. This copy does not correspond with the original. 这抄本与原件不符。 4. I managed to root out a copy of the document. 我好不容易才找到了文件的副本。 5. Would you copy this letter for me, please? 请为我复印一下这封信好吗？', '形容词: copyable 名词复数: copies 过去式: copied 过去分词: copied 现在分词: copying 第三人称单数: copies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('type', '[taɪp]', 'n.类型；典型；铅字 v.打字', '1. I\'m unfamiliar with this type of computer. 我不熟悉这种类型的计算机。 2. There are two types of rocks in this area. 这个地区有两种类型的岩石。 3. I don\'t think she\'s the artistic type. 我认为她不属艺术家那类的人。 4. Could you type this letter for me? 你能为我打这封信吗？', '过去式: typed 过去分词: typed 现在分词: typing 第三人称单数: types');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('owing', '[\'oʊɪŋ]', 'adj.未付的；归因于…的 动词owe的现在分词.', '1. There is still 2 dollars owing. 还欠着2美元。 2. Some roads are closed owing to drifting. 有些道路因积雪而封闭。 3. Owing to the rain, the match was cancelled. 由于下雨，取消了比赛。 4. The mine was closed owing to exhaustion. 这个煤矿因矿源枯竭而被关闭。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mortal', '[\'mɔːrtl]', 'adj.致命的；终有一死的；不共戴天的；极度的 n.凡人', '1. His injuries proved mortal. 他的伤成了致命伤。 2. He received a mortal wound soon after the battle began. 战争开始后不久, 他就受到了致命的重伤。 3. Man is mortal. 人都是会死的。 4. The antagonisms between the two empires and systems were mortal. 这两个帝国和两种制度之间，有着不共戴天的仇恨。 5. No mortal could vie with Zeus. 任何凡人都没法与宙斯匹敌。', '副词: mortally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('entertainment', '[ˌentər\'teɪnmənt]', 'n.娱乐', '1. There are few entertainments in that town. 那个镇上几乎没有娱乐设施。 2. Television provides universal entertainment. 电视提供大众化的娱乐。 3. Wrestling is in a twilight zone between sport and entertainment. 摔跤是介於运动和娱乐两者之间的活动。 4. This hotel is famous for its entertainment. 这家旅馆以殷勤待客著称。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flee', '[fliː]', 'vi.逃走；消失；逃避；(时间)飞逝 vt.逃离', '1. He tried to flee from the police in a stolen car. 他企图驾驶一辆偷来的车从警察局逃走。 2. The frightened people fled from the fire. 人们惊恐万状地逃离了火灾现场。 3. The mists was fleeing before the rising sun. 太阳慢慢升起，薄雾渐渐消失。 4. He should not flee from responsibility. 他不应逃避责任。 5. He was caught trying to flee the country. 他企图逃离该国时被抓住了。', '名词: fleer 过去式: fled 过去分词: fled 现在分词: fleeing 第三人称单数: flees');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beard', '[bɪrd]', 'n.胡须 vt.公开反对；抓住胡须', '1. Why don\'t you shave your beard off? 你怎麽不把胡子刮掉? 2. To my great amusement his false beard fell off. 使我感到极其好笑的是他的假胡子掉下来了。 3. He thought I was not brave enough to beard him, but he was wrong because I did it. 他以为我没有那么大勇气向他挑战，但是他错了，我就这么做了。 4. He bearded his boss and demanded an explanation. 他公然蔑视上司，并要求他作出解释。', '形容词: bearded 名词: beardedness 过去式: bearded 过去分词: bearded 现在分词: bearding 第三人称单数: beards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('helmet', '[\'helmɪt]', 'n.头盔；安全帽', '1. The sword bit the knight\'s helmet. 剑刺穿了武士的头盔。 2. A miner\'s lamp is fixed onto his helmet. 矿灯固定在矿工的头盔上。 3. The safety helmet is held on by an elastic strap. 安全帽用一根松紧带系住。 4. All visitors to the site must wear safety helmet. 到工地的所有参观者必须带上安全帽。', '形容词: helmeted 过去式: helmeted 过去分词: helmeted 现在分词: helmeting 第三人称单数: helmets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('frog', '[frɔːɡ]', 'n.蛙；嗓音沙哑；马的蹄叉；刀剑的挂环', '1. The witch changed the prince into a frog. 巫婆把王子变成了青蛙。 2. We call the breast-stroke the frog style. 我们称蛙泳为蛙式。 3. He sang with a frog in his throat. 他用略带沙哑的嗓音唱歌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resume', '[rɪ\'zuːm]', 'v.重新开始；再继续 n.简历；履历；摘要', '1. We resumed our work after a rest. 休息之后我们重新开始工作。 2. I tried to persuade her to resume her job as secretary. 我试图劝她重新干她的秘书工作。 3. Two days later, they resumed their journey. 两天以後,他们继续旅行。 4. We\'ll stop now and resume at two o\'clock. 我们现在停下来, 到两点再干。 5. I enclosed my resume in my letter. 我在信里附上了我的简历。', '形容词: resumable 名词: resumer 过去式: resumed 过去分词: resumed 现在分词: resuming 第三人称单数: resumes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('width', '[wɪdθ]', 'n.宽度；广度；宽阔', '1. The garden is six meters in width. 花园的宽度为六米。 2. He paced out the length and width of the room. 他用步子量出那房间的长度和宽度。 3. The width measurement is 80 cm. 宽为80厘米。 4. Each fold in the skirt should be exactly the same width. 裙子上的每条褶都应该一样宽。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('packet', '[\'pækɪt]', 'n.小袋；邮船；数据包', '1. The Government has clapped an extra ten pence on a packet of cigarettes. 政府对每包香烟额外提价十便士。 2. The postman tried to crush the packet through the letter-box. 邮递员使劲把邮件塞进信箱里。 3. There will be a packet to Calais. 明天有邮船开到加莱去。 4. The marshaling packet identifies an unknown object. 整理数据包识别了一个未知对象。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('likelihood', '[\'laɪklihʊd]', 'n.可能性', '1. There is no likelihood of his succeeding. 他没有成功的可能性。 2. The likelihood for peace in the Middle East remains questionable. 中东和平的可能性仍让人怀疑。 3. The likelihood of completing the research on schedule is low. 按时完成任务的可能性很小。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('solid', '[\'sɑːlɪd]', 'adj.固体的；实心的；结实的；可靠的 n.固体；立体图形 adv.一致地', '1. Ice is water in solid state. 冰是水的固体状态。 2. In fact, it was originally a solid rock. 其实,这本来是实心的岩石。 3. All these have laid a solid political foundation for consolidated national unity. 所有这些为巩固国家统一奠定了坚实的政治基础。 4. You should present solid evidence to prove your point. 你应该提供有说服力的证据来证明你的观点。 5. Water becomes solid when it freezes. 水结冰时便变成固体。', '副词: solidly 比较级: solider 最高级: solidest 名词: solidness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ink', '[ɪŋk]', 'n.墨水；墨汁', '1. There\'s an ink stain on your shirt. 你的衬衫上有一个墨水斑。 2. He has run out of red ink. 他的红墨水用完了。 3. He swore at the boy who dropped ink on the book. 他对那把墨水倒翻在书上的孩子臭骂了一顿。 4. If the ink sinks in it\'ll be hard to remove it. 如果墨水渗入，要除去就很困难。', '形容词: inky 名词: inker 过去式: inked 过去分词: inked 现在分词: inking 第三人称单数: inks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('western', '[\'westərn]', 'adj.西方的；西洋的；西部的 n.西方人；西部片；西部小说', '1. Britain has allied itself with other western powers for trade and defence. 英国与其他西方强国结成了贸易及防御联盟。 2. Silk handkerchiefs embroidered by hand sell well in the Western market. 手绣的丝制手帕在西方市场销路很好。 3. America is a western country. 美国是一个西方国家。 4. How does Chinese chess differ from western chess? 象棋和西洋棋有什么不同? 5. India is a mysterious land in the mind of Western. 在西方人的心目中，印度是一片神秘的土地。', '名词: westernness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conservative', '[kən\'sɜːrvətɪv]', 'adj.保守的；守旧的 n.保守派(党)；保守的人', '1. He was very conservative in the estimate. 他的这一估计很保守。 2. Old people are usually more conservative than young people. 老年人通常比年轻人保守。 3. The professor\'s a radical in politics but a conservative dresser. 教授在政治上是激进派,但衣着却很守旧。 4. The man turned from Radical to Conservative. 这人从激进派变成了保守派。', '副词: conservatively 名词: conservativeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('highland', '[\'haɪlənd]', 'adj.高地的 n.高地 Highland. adj.苏格兰高地的', '1. Those people live in highland regions. 那些人住在高地地区。 2. The guerrilla force captured the highland in two hours. 游击队两个小时之内就占领了高地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fool', '[fuːl]', 'n.傻瓜；小丑；奶油果蓉 v.愚弄；欺骗；开玩笑；干蠢事；玩弄；鬼混', '1. What a fool I was to believe he is a good man. 我竟然相信他是个好人，我真是个傻瓜。 2. I am a fool to have refused the job. 我真傻,拒绝了那项工作。 3. He played the fool to entertain the king in that opera. 在那部歌剧中他扮演小丑来逗国王开心。 4. He is trying to fool you,don\'t listen to him. 他想愚弄你，别听他的。', '过去式: fooled 过去分词: fooled 现在分词: fooling 第三人称单数: fools');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('freeze', '[friːz]', 'v.冻结；冷冻；僵硬；凝固 n.严寒；冻结', '1. Water freezes at the temperature of 0 degrees Celsius. 水在摄氏零度结冰。 2. We ate some of the fruits and froze the rest. 我们吃了一些水果，把剩下的冷藏起来。 3. They freeze this theory to death. 他们把这个理论僵化了。 4. The quality of the imagination is to flow and not to freeze. 想象的特点是流动,而不是凝固。 5. He slipped and broke his leg during the big freeze. 他在严寒期间滑倒,摔断了腿。', '形容词: freezable 过去式: froze 过去分词: frozen 现在分词: freezing 第三人称单数: freezes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pedal', '[\'pedl]', 'n.踏板；乐器的脚踏键 v.用脚踏动；踩踏板', '1. The pedal of a cycle is attached to a crank. 自行车的踏板与曲柄相连。 2. He pushed hard on the brake pedal to avoid a collision. 他使劲踩下煞车踏板以避免撞车。 3. He had to pedal hard to get up the hill. 他得用力踩动，以便上山。 4. I saw him pedal to school every morning. 我看到他每天早晨骑自行车上学。', '过去式: pedaled/pedalled 过去分词: pedaled/pedalled 现在分词: pedaling/pedalling 第三人称单数: pedals/pedals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('musical', '[\'mjuːzɪkl]', 'adj.音乐的；喜欢音乐的；悦耳的 n.音乐片', '1. The mother found that her son had a musical talent. 母亲发现儿子有音乐天赋。 2. Since he can play many musical instruments, he may well be called a man of accomplishments. 他能演奏许多乐器，当然称得上是个多才多艺的人。 3. Everyone in my family is very musical. 我家所有人都很喜欢音乐。 4. A musical bell softly sounded somewhere in the passageway. 走廊的某处响起轻柔悦耳的铃声。 5. Carroll appeared in a number of Broadway musicals. 卡洛尔演出了一系列百老汇音乐剧。', '副词: musically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poem', '[\'poʊəm]', 'n.诗；韵文', '1. He wrote a poem praising her loveliness. 他写了一首诗赞扬她的美丽。 2. The girl repeated the poem after I had read it twice. 我读了两遍这首诗，这个小女孩就会背诵了。 3. The poem showed great intensity of feeling. 这篇韵文表现出强烈的激情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gently', '[\'dʒentli]', 'adv.轻轻地；温柔地，文雅地，有礼貌地；和缓地；高贵地', '1. He rotates the handle gently. 他轻轻地转动手柄。 2. The waves gently lap against the shore. 海浪轻轻地拍打着海岸。 3. She caressed his hair very gently. 她温柔地抚摸他的头发。 4. She held the bird gently in her palm. 她将鸟儿温柔地捧在她的手掌心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('foresee', '[fɔːr\'siː]', 'v.预见；预知', '1. Can you foresee what will happen in the future? 你能预见将来会发生什么吗? 2. Nobody could foresee his running away. 没人预见到他的逃跑。 3. Few analysts foresaw that oil prices would rise so steeply. 几乎没有分析师能预见的到石油价格会上升得这么快。 4. Those who can foresee difficulties on their way to success may keep calm when they really appear. 在走向成功的路途中能够预见到困难的人在困难真正出现的时候常常能保持冷静的态度。', '形容词: foreseeable 名词: foreseer 过去式: foresaw 过去分词: foreseen 现在分词: foreseeing 第三人称单数: foresees');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rag', '[ræɡ]', 'n.破布；碎布；破衣服；（低劣的）报纸', '1. She twisted a rag round my hand. 她用一块破布包住我的手。 2. He plugged the hole in the pipe with an old rag. 他用一块旧破布把管子上的那个洞塞住了。 3. He wrapped a clean rag around his ankle. 他把一小块乾净的布缠住脚腕。 4. It\'s just an old rag I had in the closet. 这只不过是我挂在壁橱里的旧衣服罢了。', '过去式: ragged 过去分词: ragged 现在分词: ragging 第三人称单数: rags');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('basement', '[\'beɪsmənt]', 'n.根基；地下室', '1. Dam Monitoring Dam monitoring at a mountain water reservoir during the basement stablization. 大坝监测水库大坝监测在根基稳定期间。 2. The dampness in the basement damaged his books. 地下室的潮湿将他的书损坏了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clothing', '[\'kloʊðɪŋ]', 'n.(总称)衣服；覆盖物', '1. He discarded his winter clothing. 他把冬天穿的衣服都丢弃了。 2. This clothing sells well to the teenage market. 这种衣服在青少年中间很畅销。 3. Children depend on their parents for food and clothing. 小孩依赖他们的父母供给衣食。 4. We have to put on warm clothing in winter. 冬天的时候，我们不得不穿上温暖的衣服。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yellow', '[\'jeloʊ]', 'adj.黄色的 n.黄色；蛋黄；黄种人 v.（使）变黄', '1. The leaves turn yellow in autumn. 秋天时叶子变黄。 2. The leaves of the book had yellowed with age. 书页因年久而变黄。 3. She wore on her head a yellow kerchief. 她头上带着一块黄色的头巾。 4. Sunflowers are large flowers with yellow petals. 向日葵是长着黄色花瓣的大花。 5. Yellow is the prevailing color in her room. 黄色是她房间的主色。 6. The pages of the book began to yellow. 书页开始发黄了。', '比较级: yellower 最高级: yellowest 名词: yellowness 过去式: yellowed 过去分词: yellowed 现在分词: yellowing 第三人称单数: yellows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cable', '[\'keɪbl]', 'n.电缆；缆；索；电报 v.发电报；(通过电缆)交流；(用缆绳)固定', '1. Cable television has been around for some time now. 有线电视面世已有些时日了。 2. They are building a submarine cable tunnel. 他们正在建设一条海底电缆隧道。 3. A number of cables are needed in this project. 这项工程需要大量电缆。 4. Try replacing the cable with a known working cable. 试著以确定是工作良好的缆线替换缆线。 5. News of his death was cabled to his family. 他的死讯已电告其家属。', '名词: cabler 过去式: cabled 过去分词: cabled 现在分词: cabling 第三人称单数: cables');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('specify', '[\'spesɪfaɪ]', 'v.详细说明；指定；阐述', '1. Please specify when you will be at home tomorrow. 请确切说明你明天何时会在家。 2. Also, you might have to specify the user name and password. 另外,您可能还需要指定用户名和密码。 3. Please specify the whole process of the project. 请阐述下这个项目的整个过程。', '名词: specifier 过去式: specified 过去分词: specified 现在分词: specifying 第三人称单数: specifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('twist', '[twɪst]', 'v.缠绕；捻；搓；拧；扭曲 n.拧；捻；扭曲；盘旋；弯曲处', '1. She twisted the long scarf round her head. 她把那条长围巾围在头上。 2. Selecting the suitable twist factor in order to meet the needs of flax knitting yarn, it is the key to increase high_grade and productivity of flax knitting products. 选择合理的捻系数以满足针织用纱的要求是提高亚麻针织产品档次和生产效率的关键。 3. We twisted the bed sheets into a rope and escaped by climbing down it. 我们把床单搓成绳子，援绳下坠逃跑了。 4. The cap should twist off easily. 这个帽儿应该容易拧开。 5. She gave the lid another twist and it came off. 她又拧了一下，盖儿开了。', '形容词: twistable 副词: twistingly 名词: twistability 过去式: twisted 过去分词: twisted 现在分词: twisting 第三人称单数: twists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acceptance', '[ək\'septəns]', 'n.认可；同意；承兑；接受（礼物、邀请、建议等）', '1. The proposal met with general acceptance. 这个建议得到普遍的认可。 2. The idea rapidly gained acceptance in political circles. 这一想法很快得到了政界的认可。 3. The proposal was met with general acceptance. 这建议得到普遍的赞同。 4. We usually only discount acceptance trade and commercial bills. 我们通常只贴现已承兑的商业票据。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deceit', '[dɪ\'siːt]', 'n.欺骗；诡计；不诚实', '1. She told him of his old mother\'s deceit. 她向他诉说了母后的欺骗行为。 2. Deceit is a gift, but vengeance is swift. 欺骗可能会获得短暂的利益，但报复也会迅速地随之而来。 3. He was enmeshed in a web of deceit and lies. 他陷入充满诡计和谎言的圈套。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compare', '[kəm\'per]', 'v.比较；对比；比喻 n.比较；对照', '1. I compared the copy with the original, but there was not much difference. 我比较了复印件和原件，但是差别不是很大。 2. The police compared the suspect\'s fingerprints with those found at the crime scene. 警察将嫌疑犯的指纹和犯罪现场的指纹进行了对比。 3. Life is poetically compared to the morning dew. 在诗歌中，人生被比喻为朝露。 4. She is lovely beyond compare. 她真是可爱得无与伦比。', '名词: comparer 过去式: compared 过去分词: compared 现在分词: comparing 第三人称单数: compares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('patient', '[\'peɪʃnt]', 'adj.有耐心的；能忍耐的 n.病人', '1. You\'ll have to be patient with my mother she\'s going rather deaf. 你对我母亲得有耐心，她的耳朵越来越背了。 2. He is a patient man, but not even he could sit down under that kind of provocation. 他是一个能忍耐的人，但就连他也没法忍受那种挑衅了。 3. To have access to the good things of the world, one has to be patient and wait. 对于世间美好的东西,忍耐与等待是不可缺少的。 4. After patient explanations, he carried all the members with him on that proposal. 他通过耐心解释，说服了所有成员接受了他的那项建议。 5. The patient began to gain ground as soon as she had good food. 这位病人饮食一好，她的病情就开始好转了。', '副词: patiently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('official', '[ə\'fɪʃl]', 'adj.正式的；官方的；公务上的 n.官员', '1. The group have split off from the official union. 这一部分人已从正式的联盟中分裂出来了。 2. I happen to have the official statistics with me. 我碰巧身边有官方的统计数字。 3. They expressed their dissent from official policy. 他们对官方的政策表示出异议。 4. He settled down again to the official mail. 他又安下心来，处理那些公务邮件。 5. He is a pompous official. 他是个自命不凡的官员。', '副词: officially 名词: officialdom');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('waterfall', '[\'wɔːtərfɔːl]', 'n.瀑布', '1. We saw a few salmon jumping in the waterfall there. 我们看到那边瀑布里几条鲑鱼在跳。 2. They were filled with wonder at the new waterfall. 他们对新瀑布感到非常惊奇。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('majority', '[mə\'dʒɔːrəti]', 'n.大多数；多数；多数党；多数派', '1. The majority of people seem to prefer TV to radio. 多数人喜欢电视胜过广播。 2. Racism is abhorrent to the majority of people. 种族主义是大多数人都憎恨的。 3. The Democrats became the majority in the election. 民主党在这次选举中变成了多数党。 4. The Democrats became the majority in the election. 民主党在这次选举中变成了多数党。', '名词复数: majorities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('busy', '[\'bɪzi]', 'adj.忙的；繁忙的；热闹的；(电话)占线的 vt.使忙于', '1. He is busy with some important work. 他正忙于处理一些重要的事情。 2. He was busy getting ready for his journey. 他正忙于准备旅行。 3. The shop looked out into a busy street. 这商店濒临近一条繁忙的街道。 4. The traffic was at its height at the busy junction. 在繁忙的交叉路口，车辆来往正处于高峰。 5. To forget his trouble, he busied himself in his garden . 为了把烦恼忘却，他让自己忙于花园的工作。', '副词: busily 比较级: busier 最高级: busiest 名词: busyness 过去式: busied 过去分词: busied 现在分词: busying 第三人称单数: busies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hollow', '[\'hɑːloʊ]', 'adj.空的；空洞的；凹陷的；虚伪的；(声音)沉闷的 n.山谷；洞；窟窿 vt.挖空 vi.形成空洞 adv.完全地；彻底', '1. This tree looks high and strong but actually its trunk is hollow. 这棵树看起来又高又壮，实际上树干是空的。 2. His protests on human rights sound hollow. 他就人权问题提出的抗议听来很空洞。 3. He was thin and his cheeks were hollow. 他很瘦,连面颊都凹陷了下去。 4. An open enemy is better than a hollow friend. 宁有公开的敌人，不要虚伪的朋友。 5. The track dipped, weaving into a wooded hollow. 小路消失了，迂回前行到了一片多树的山谷里。 6. The Indians used to hollow out a log to make a canoe. 印第安人过去常挖空圆木制成独木舟。 7. I played Max at chess yesterday and beat him hollow. 昨天我跟麦克斯下棋，杀得他一败涂地。', '副词: hollowly 比较级: hollower 最高级: hollowest 名词: hollowness 过去式: hollowed 过去分词: hollowed 现在分词: hollowing 第三人称单数: hollows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('humid', '[\'hjuːmɪd]', 'adj.潮湿的', '1. The humid climate didn\'t agree with him. 那潮湿的气候对他不合适。 2. She thought of her humid, stuffy darkroom. 她想起了自己那间闷热潮湿的暗室。', '副词: humidly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('indifferent', '[ɪn\'dɪfrənt]', 'adj.漠不关心的；无关紧要的；平凡的；中立的', '1. He is indifferent to the result of the exam. 他对考试结果漠不关心。 2. She seems indifferent, but deep down she\'s very pleased. 她貌似无动於衷，其实心里非常高兴。 3. Many one or little one is indifferent to me. 多一个或少一个对我是无关紧要的。 4. It was utterly indifferent to her who he was. 封她来说，他是谁，根本是无关紧要的事。', '副词: indifferently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fashionable', '[\'fæʃnəbl]', 'adj.流行的；时髦的', '1. We have some fashionable patterns here. 我们这儿有些流行的款式。 2. She likes to wear fashionable clothes. 她喜欢穿流行的衣服。 3. These fashionable jackets are rather expensive. 这些时髦的夹克衫相当贵。 4. It was performed in fashionable Casino ballrooms. 人们在时髦的娱乐舞厅里跳这种舞蹈。', '副词: fashionably 名词: fashionability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('policeman', '[pə\'liːsmən]', 'n.（男）警察', '1. The policeman watched his quarry go into a bar. 警察看著他在追捕的人走进一家酒吧。 2. The wounded policeman is now out of danger. 受伤的警察已经脱离危险。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('five', '[faɪv]', 'num.五', '1. My company is five miles distant from my home. 公司距离我家五英里远。 2. That car went out of production five years ago. 那种汽车已经停产五年了。 3. Linda has to commute about five miles to the city. 玛丽每天得走约五英里的路去城里上班。 4. We\'ve got to fit five people plus all their luggage in the car. 我们得在汽车里挤下五个人和全部行李。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('susceptible', '[sə\'septəbl]', 'adj.易受外界影响的；易受感染的；容许…的', '1. Children are more susceptible than adults. 孩子比成人易受外界的影响。 2. Some people are susceptible to advertising. 一些人易受广告的影响。 3. The plant is not susceptible to disease. 这种植物不容易受病害侵袭。 4. Children are susceptible to various illnesses. 孩子易患各种疾病。', '副词: susceptibly 名词: susceptibleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ban', '[bæn]', 'v.禁止；剥夺权利 n.禁令；禁止', '1. The government has banned the use of chemical weapons. 政府已经禁止使用化学武器。 2. She was banned from athletics for two years after failing a drug test. 她在药检中被查出服用禁用药物而被禁赛两年。 3. A ban on the importation of drugs has been issued recently. 最近已经发布了禁止进口毒品的法令。 4. There is a ban on smoking in the theatre. 这剧院内禁止吸烟。', '名词复数: bani 过去式: banned 过去分词: banned 现在分词: banning 第三人称单数: bans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('past', '[pæst]', 'prep.过；经过 adv.过 adj.过去的 n.过去；昔日；过去的事情；过去的经历；往事', '1. It is past my power. 这是我力所不及的。 2. It was past midnight when we got home. 我们到家时已过半夜. 3. He hurried past me without stopping. 他匆忙从我身边走过，连停都没停。 4. They walked past without stopping 他们一步不停地走了过去。 5. His pain is past now. 他的痛苦现在已经过去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spicy', '[\'spaɪsi]', 'adj.辛辣的；香的', '1. Spicy food does not agree with me. 辛辣食物不合我的胃口。 2. The cookies were rich and spicy. 这些小甜饼油多味香。', '副词: spicily 比较级: spicier 最高级: spiciest 名词: spiciness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('process', '[\'prɑˌsɛs]', 'n.工序；过程 v.加工；处理；起诉；列队前进', '1. Building a car is a long process. 制造一辆小汽车有很长的工序。 2. They went over every process again, but without result. 他们把每道工序又检查了一遍，却仍没有结果。 3. Growth and decay are vital processes. 生长和衰亡是生命过程。 4. Brazil began importing soybeans to process at home. 巴西开始进口大豆在国内加工。', '名词复数: processes 过去式: processed 过去分词: processed 现在分词: processing 第三人称单数: processes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stay', '[steɪ]', 'v.停留；逗留；保持 n.停留；逗留', '1. I stayed late at the party last night. 昨晚我在晚会上呆到很晚。 2. You can stay at home and watch TV. 你可以待在家里并且看电视。 3. Why don\'t you come to stay with us next time you visit Durham? 下次来达勒姆就住在我们这儿好吗? 4. The temperature has stayed hot this week. 本周气温一直都很热。 5. He went straight to New York without a stay in Hongkong. 他直接去了纽约,没在香港停留。', '过去式: stayed 过去分词: stayed 现在分词: staying 第三人称单数: stays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('neutral', '[\'nuːtrəl]', 'adj.中立的；中性的；空档的；素净色的 n.中立者；空挡位置', '1. That country remained neutral in the war. 那个国家在那场战争中保持中立。 2. He has a rather neutral character. 他品性平平。 3. When you start the engine, be sure the car is in neutral. 你在发动引擎时，一定要让汽车处于空档。 4. A neutral tie can be worn with a shirt of any colour. 暗灰色的领带配什麽颜色的衬衣都行。 5. For Britain, Switzerland was a useful and friendly neutral. 对英国来说,瑞士是一个有利和友好的中立国。', '副词: neutrally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('knob', '[nɑːb]', 'n.旋钮；把手；瘤；节；圆丘', '1. Twist the knob to the right setting. 把旋钮拧到适当的定位挡上。 2. As he turned the knob, the sound diminished. 他一转旋钮，声音就变小了。 3. You may turn the right knob on the TV to switch it on. 你可以拧电视上右边的旋钮把它打开。 4. He could not find the knob in the dark. 黑暗中，他无法找到门把手。', '形容词: knobbed');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('canal', '[kə\'næl]', 'n.运河；沟渠；气管；食管 vt.建运河；疏导', '1. The canal is now open to shipping. 该运河现已通航。 2. They dragged the canal for the missing child. 他们用拖网沿运河打捞失踪孩子的尸体。 3. The canal is navigable all the year. 这条运河全年可通航。 4. Many oceangoing ships are sailing on the canal. 许多远洋船只在这条运河上航行。 5. The workers canal an isthmus. 工人们在地峡处开凿了一条运河。', '过去式: canalled/canaled 过去分词: canalled/canaled 现在分词: canalling/canaling 第三人称单数: canals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hook', '[hʊk]', 'n.钩；钩状物；勾拳 v.钩住；弯成(钩状)；当妓女', '1. Please hang your coat on the hook. 请把你的外衣挂在钩上。 2. They took the phone off the hook so no calls would disturb them. 他们摘下电话听筒，以免电话打扰他们。 3. He smote his match to the ground with a left hook. 他以一记左钩拳把对手击倒在地。 4. Please hook the rope over the nail. 请把绳子挂在那根钉子上。', '过去式: hooked 过去分词: hooked 现在分词: hooking 第三人称单数: hooks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cashier', '[kæ\'ʃɪr]', 'n.出纳员；收银员 vt.解职；丢弃', '1. The robber threatened the cashier with a revolver. 强盗用左轮手枪威胁出纳员。 2. The cashier juggled the accounts to hide his theft. 那个出纳员窜改帐目,企图隐瞒他盗用钱款的行径。 3. The cashier checked out and bagged my order. 收款员计价收款并给我包装了商品 4. I work at a bookstore as a cashier once a week. 我一个星期去一次书店做收银员。 5. He has been cashiered because he was caught cheating at cards. 因为打牌做弊,他被解职了。', '过去式: cashiered 过去分词: cashiered 现在分词: cashiering 第三人称单数: cashiers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cloudy', '[\'klaʊdi]', 'adj.多云的；阴天的；混浊的；模糊不清的', '1. Tonight will be cloudy. 今天夜间多云。 2. In that cloudy sky only one lone star can be seen. 在那多云的天上，只能看到孤零零的一颗星星。 3. It\'s cloudy today. 今天阴天。 4. A drop of milk diffused in the water, and it became cloudy. 一滴奶在水中扩散开来，使水变得混浊不清了。', '副词: cloudily 比较级: cloudier 最高级: cloudiest 名词: cloudiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('widespread', '[\'waɪdspred]', 'adj.分布(或散布)广的；普遍的', '1. The high cost prohibits the widespread use of the drug. 该药因价格昂贵而影响其被广泛应用。 2. Widespread flooding is affecting large areas of Devon. 洪水泛滥，淹没了德文郡的广大地区。 3. The Government acted quickly to relieve the widespread distress caused by the earthquake. 地震造成大范围的灾难,政府迅速采取行动赈济灾民。 4. The new laws gained widespread acceptance. 新法例广获赞同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('e-mail', '[iː meɪl]', 'n.电子邮件', '1. Electronic mail,for instance,has improved management efficiency tremendously. 拿电子邮件来说，现在和没有电子邮件的时代是完全两样。 2. Electronic mail will soon play a dominant role in transmittingmessages. 电子邮件很快会在信息传输方面起主导作用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('puff', '[pʌf]', 'vt.喷出；喘息；夸张；膨胀；吹捧 vi.喷出；膨胀；喘息；骄傲 n.一阵；一股；粉扑；泡芙 adj.吹嘘的', '1. Don\'t puff cigarette smoke in my face. 不要向我脸上喷烟。 2. He managed to puff out a few words. 他喘息着说出几句话。 3. Such lost souls puff themselves up into grand monsters. 这些迷失的灵魂将自己膨胀成大怪物。 4. All due to nonphysical forces vying to puff themselves up the dimensions thinking that this is what ascension is. 所有的灭绝，均缘于非物质力量试图来将自己在各密度膨胀，并认为这就是提升的缘故。 5. Smoke puffed from the chimney. 烟从烟囱里一股一股地喷出来。 6. A puff of wind blew out the candle. 一阵风吹熄了蜡烛。', '形容词: puffy 副词: puffily 名词: puffiness 过去式: puffed 过去分词: puffed 现在分词: puffing 第三人称单数: puffs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lounge', '[laʊndʒ]', 'n.休息室；候机室；起居室 v.闲荡；懒散地斜靠', '1. We watched television in the hotel lounge. 我们在旅馆休息室里看电视。 2. Please move forward to the passenger lounge . 请向前走到旅客休息室。 3. She is waiting for me in the departure lounge. 她在候机室等我。 4. The children have made an awful mess in the lounge. 孩子们把起居室弄得凌乱不堪。 5. I don\'t want to lounge about town. I have other things to do. 我不想在市区闲逛。我还有别的事要做。', '名词: lounger 过去式: lounged 过去分词: lounged 现在分词: lounging 第三人称单数: lounges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('highlight', '[\'haɪlaɪt]', 'vt.强调；照亮；加亮；使 ... 显得重要；使突出 n.加亮区；精彩部分；最重要的细节或事件；闪光点 [计算机] 醒目', '1. Both books highlight the human element of science. 两本书都重点谈到科学中人的因素。 2. Mr Bush also wants to highlight African successes. 布什先生想突出强调一下非洲的成就。 3. What would you highlight about them? 对于他们你想强调些什么呢? 4. Of course we must highlight that the system can hardly be inaccurate. 当然我们必须强调这一点，即该系统根本不可能出错。 5. It is one of the highlights of the match. 这是比赛中最精彩的项目之一。', '过去式: highlighted 过去分词: highlighted 现在分词: highlighting 第三人称单数: highlights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('decimal', '[\'desɪml]', 'adj.小数的；十进位的 n.小数', '1. The first two figures after the decimal point indicate tenths and hundredths respectively. 小数点后的头两位数分别表示十分位和百分位。 2. Most countries have a decimal currency. 大多数国家使用十进制货币。 3. There were only decimal math problem on the quiz. 测验中只有十进位的数学题。 4. Britain converted to a decimal currency system in 1971. 英国于1971年改行十进制货币体系。 5. 0.3 is a decimal. 0.', '副词: decimally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('achieve', '[ə\'tʃiːv]', 'v.完成；达到；实现', '1. I\'ve achieved only half of what I\'d hoped to do. 我希望做到的,我仅完成了一半。 2. Work hard, and you will achieve your goal. 好好干,你就会达到自己的目标。 3. You will achieve your ambition if you work hard. 如果你努力, 你的抱负是可以实现的。', '形容词: achievable 名词: achiever 过去式: achieved 过去分词: achieved 现在分词: achieving 第三人称单数: achieves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('toxic', '[\'tɑːksɪk]', 'adj.有毒的', '1. The factory had been sending out toxic fumes. 这家工厂一直在排放有毒的废气。 2. The toxic gas is extremely dangerous. 有毒的汽体是非常地危险的。 3. Too much toxic waste is being dumped at sea. 太多的有毒废料在向大海里倾倒。', '副词: toxically 名词: toxin');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('table', '[\'teɪbl]', 'n.桌子；台子；餐桌；一桌人；表格；目录；（竞赛的）排名榜 vt.搁置；将 ... 放于桌上；提交讨论；列入表中 adj.桌子的', '1. He moved the table over to the center of the room. 他把桌子移到房间中心。 2. Mother told me to lay the table for breakfast. 母亲让我摆好桌子准备吃早饭。 3. We prefer a table besides the window in non-smoking. 我们要不抽烟区靠窗的台子。 4. She spread a cloth on the table. 她用一块布铺在餐桌上。 5. They voted to table the proposal until the following meeting. 他们投票决定把这项建议留到下次会议讨论。', '过去式: tabled 过去分词: tabled 现在分词: tabling 第三人称单数: tables');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('despair', '[dɪ\'sper]', 'n.绝望；失望 vi.失望', '1. A person is most disappointed when he is in despair. 一个人在绝望时最失望。 2. He has been in the abyss of despair. 他已陷入绝望的深渊。 3. He fluctuated between hope and despair. 他时而充满希望时而失望。 4. He is the despair of all other pianists. 他使其他所有的钢琴家都感到失望。 5. We cannot despair of humanity, since we are ourselves human beings. 身为人类,我们不能对人性失望。', '过去式: despaired 过去分词: despaired 现在分词: despairing 第三人称单数: despairs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overtake', '[ˌoʊvər\'teɪk]', 'v.赶上；突然来袭；压倒', '1. The car pulled out to overtake the lorry. 小汽车开出车道去超那辆卡车。 2. I had to walk very fast to overtake you. 我不得不快走才能赶过你。 3. It\'s dangerous to overtake on a bend. 在转弯处超车十分危险。 4. For no man knows what misfortunes may overtake you. 因为谁都不知道你会遭到什么不幸。', '过去式: overtook 过去分词: overtaken 现在分词: overtaking 第三人称单数: overtakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disastrous', '[dɪ\'zæstrəs]', 'adj.灾难性的；极糟的', '1. The new system has had a disastrous effect on productivity. 新制度已对生产力造成了灾难性的影响。 2. This environmental effect of this new factory could be disastrous. 这家新工厂给自然环境带来的影响可能是灾难性的。 3. Such a mistake would perhaps lead to disastrous consequences. 这样一种错误可能导致灾难性的后果。 4. The economic position of the country is disastrous. 国家的经济形势非常糟糕。', '副词: disastrously 名词: disastrousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drawing', '[\'drɔːɪŋ]', 'n.图画；素描；绘图；拉伸 n.抽签 动词draw的现在分词形式.', '1. Join the dots up to complete the drawing. 顺点连线把图画好。 2. You jogged my elbow and spoiled what I was drawing. 你撞到了我的手肘，弄坏了我正在画的图画。 3. He did/made a drawing of the old farmhouse. 他画了一幅古老农舍的素描。 4. She studies one drawing of a nude girl. 她认真看着一个裸体少女的素描。 5. If the scores are still equal, ranking will be decided by lots drawing. 如仍然相同，则以抽签决定名次。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('instant', '[\'ɪnstənt]', 'n.瞬间；立即 adj.立即的；即时的；速成的', '1. I shall be back in an instant. 我马上就回来。 2. Just for an instant I thought he was going to refuse. 我脑中有一闪念，以为他要拒绝了。 3. I recognized her the instant I saw her. 我一眼就认出是她。 4. Come here this instant! 请马上到这里来！ 5. I took an instant dislike to him. 我一见他就不喜欢。', '名词: instantness 副词: instantly 形容词: instantaneous');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deadly', '[\'dedli]', 'adj.致命的；如死一样的 adv.非常地；如死一般地', '1. Cancer is a deadly disease. 癌症是一种致命的疾病。 2. Fog is the sailor\'s deadly enemy. 雾是航海者最致命的敌人。 3. The accident subjected her to a deadly blow. 这次意外使她受到致命的打击。 4. The conference was deadly dull. 会议开得死气沉沉的。 5. Mary is finding life deadly monotonous . 玛丽感到生活非常单调。', '比较级: deadlier 最高级: deadliest 名词: deadliness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deliberate', '[dɪ\'lɪbərət]', 'adj.深思熟虑的；故意的；从容不迫的 v.仔细考虑；研讨', '1. She has a slow, deliberate way of talking. 她谈话的方式缓慢而审慎. 2. He told us a deliberate lie. 他存心说谎。 3. It had more the appearance of a deliberate crime than an accident. 那很像是蓄意的罪行，而不像是意外的事故。 4. He entered the room with deliberate steps. 他从容不迫地走进室内。 5. We had no time to deliberate on the problem. 我们没有时间仔细思考这个问题.', '副词: deliberately 名词: deliberateness 过去式: deliberated 过去分词: deliberated 现在分词: deliberating 第三人称单数: deliberates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('put', '[pʊt]', 'v.放；安置；使处于；提交；记下；表达；出发；开航 n.推铅球；期货买卖', '1. He put his hands in his pockets. 他把手放在口袋里。 2. She put the grapes onto the platter. 她把葡萄放到一个大盘子上。 3. Put down my pen and stop fiddling! 把我的钢笔放下，别用手玩弄！ 4. I\'ve put my entire life into a sound and perfect order. 我把自己的一生都安排妥当了。', '过去式: put 过去分词: put 现在分词: putting 第三人称单数: puts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('topic', '[\'tɑːpɪk]', 'n.题目；话题；标题', '1. Lack of space forbids further treatment of the topic here. 因篇幅所限，此处不便对本题作进一步阐述。 2. This essay is so short that it can only scratch the surface of the topic. 这篇文章很短，只能对这一问题作肤浅的探讨。 3. The essay isn\'t even remotely relevant to the topic. 这篇文章毫不切题。 4. The topic seemed to have a fascination for her. 这个题目似乎对她很有吸引力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anticipate', '[æn\'tɪsɪpeɪt]', 'vt.预期；提前使用；抢 ... 前 vi.预言', '1. We anticipate that we will meet a certain amount of resistance to our plan. 我们预料我们的计划会遇到一些人的反对。 2. I anticipate reading the book with great interest. 我以极大的兴趣期待着读这本书。 3. It is unwise to anticipate your earnings by spending a lot of money. 大量花钱提前使用自己的收入是不明智的。 4. They anticipate ours by just one month. 他们比我们抢先了一个月。', '形容词: anticipatable 名词: anticipator 过去式: anticipated 过去分词: anticipated 现在分词: anticipating 第三人称单数: anticipates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('customary', '[\'kʌstəmeri]', 'adj.习惯的；惯例的', '1. That\'s his customary shortcoming. 那是他一个习惯的毛病。 2. Obviously, this has gone beyond their customary limits. 显然，这已经超出了置业习惯的限制。 3. He refused to have his portrait conventionalized into the customary smooth beauty of the pharaoh god. 他不让他的画像具有惯例的法老神的那种传统的温和的美。 4. In addition, the personal right of copyright can be restricted by the laws related, the customs, especially the professional customary practices. 此外，著作人身权还要受到相关法律和习惯，尤其是行业惯例的限制。', '副词: customarily 名词: customariness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shame', '[ʃeɪm]', 'n.羞愧；耻辱；可耻的人或物 vt.使丢脸；使羞愧；使蒙羞', '1. He had no sense of shame and never felt guilty. 他毫无羞耻之心，而且从不觉得内疚。 2. He saved the child at the risk of his own life and put all those who looked on to shame. 他冒着生命危险救了那个孩子,使所有旁观者都相形见绌。 3. Your bad behavior brings shame on the whole school. 你的恶劣行径给整个学校带来耻辱。 4. It is a shame to take money from those who can\'t afford it. 拿别人的钱使人家无以自立是十分可耻的。 5. He was shamed by how much more work the others had done. 别人做得多得多，他感到很难为情。', '过去式: shamed 过去分词: shamed 现在分词: shaming 第三人称单数: shames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aural', '[\'ɔːrəl]', 'adj.听觉的；耳的', '1. You can use these tapes as aural material. 你可以把这些磁带当作听力材料。 2. The opera was an aural as well as a visual delight. 这部歌剧对于听觉和视觉都是一种享受。', '副词: aurally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('minimum', '[\'mɪnɪməm]', 'adj.最少的；最低程度的 n.最低限度；最小量', '1. That is the minimum number necessary to complete the circuit. 这是完善循环的最低限度人数。 2. The minimum wage is 4.25 dollars an hour. 最低工价为每小时四点二五美元。 3. Repairing your car will cost a minimum of 100 dollars. 修理你的汽车最低限度要100美元。 4. The class needs a minimum of 6 pupils to continue. 这个班最低限度要六个学生才可以继续办下去。', '名词复数: minimums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('patron', '[\'peɪtrən]', 'n.赞助人；老主顾；守护神', '1. Modern artists have difficulty in finding patrons. 现代艺术家们很难找到赞助人。 2. He inscribed those poems to his patron. 他将这些诗献给他的赞助人。 3. This store has many patrons. 这家商店有许多老顾客。 4. The usher handed the patron to a reserved seat. 引座员把顾客引到预订的座位上', '形容词: patronal');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('excess', '[ɪk\'ses]', 'n.超过；过量；过剩 adj.过量的；额外的', '1. Our school has a student number in excess of 800. 我们学校的学生数超过八百人。 2. His excesses at parties are well known. 尽人皆知他在聚会上十分放肆。 3. An excess of fat in one\'s diet can lead to heart disease. 食物中脂肪过多会导致心脏病。 4. This wave of excess density is sound. 这种过剩密度的波就是声波。 5. The fat boy went on a diet to get rid of his excess weight. 这个胖男孩节制饮食以减轻过量的体重。', '过去式: excessed 过去分词: excessed 现在分词: excessing 第三人称单数: excesses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('almost', '[\'ɔːlmoʊst]', 'adv.几乎；差不多 adj.相近的', '1. He slipped and almost fell. 他脚下一滑，险些跌倒。 2. She was almost mad with grief when her son died. 她的儿子死去时，她悲伤得几乎疯了。 3. This event was almost simultaneous with that one. 这件事几乎是与那件事同时发生的。 4. It\'s almost time to go. 差不多是该走的时候了。 5. The girl was annoyed by his almost impudence. 他几近厚颜无耻的态度把那个女孩给惹恼了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trouble', '[\'trʌbəl]', 'n.困难；烦恼；麻烦 v.使烦恼；麻烦；苦恼；费神', '1. I find getting up early a great trouble. 我觉得早起床可不容易。 2. I\'m sorry to have to put you to so much trouble. 很抱歉，给您添了这麽多麻烦。 3. Don\'t mention my name or you\'ll get me into trouble. 别提我的名字，免得给我惹麻烦。 4. I\'m sorry to trouble you, but I wondered if we could have a word some time. 很遗憾要打扰你一下，我想问问我们什么时候能聊聊。', '副词: troublingly 名词: troubler 过去式: troubled 过去分词: troubled 现在分词: troubling 第三人称单数: troubles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('productivity', '[ˌprɑːdʌk\'tɪvəti]', 'n.生产率；生产力', '1. We should aim with efforts for higher productivity. 我们应该力争达到更高的生产率。 2. This will help do away with heavy manual labour and raise productivity. 这可以帮助消除繁重的体力劳动，提高劳动生产率。 3. Improved productivity justifies an increase in wages. 提高了生产力理应增加工资。 4. The workers are trying their best to increase productivity. 工人们正竭尽全力提高生产力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('duck', '[dʌk]', 'n.鸭肉；鸭；亲爱的人 v.躲避，闪开；潜入', '1. The special today is pressed duck with walnuts. 今天的特色菜是桃仁酥鸭。 2. They visited a duck farm operated by the corporation. 他们参观了这个公司办的养鸭场。 3. You cannot teach an old duck new tricks. 老鸭学不会新把戏。 4. There are many ducks swimming in the lake. 湖里有许多鸭子在游泳。', '名词: ducker 过去式: ducked 过去分词: ducked 现在分词: ducking 第三人称单数: ducks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sensible', '[\'sensəbl]', 'adj.明智的；合情理的；可觉察的；实际的 n.可感知物', '1. To wink at rudeness in children is not sensible. 对小孩粗鲁的行为视若无睹是不明智的。 2. That sounds very sensible to me. 我觉得这很合理。 3. Saving your presence, I don\'t think the suggestion is very sensible. 请恕我直言，我认为这个建议不太合情理。 4. Her distress was sensible from her manner. 她的悲痛从她的态度上可觉察到。 5. The world of dreams is our real world whilst we are sleeping because our attention then lapses from the sensible world. 在睡眠中梦见的世界便是我们的真实世界，因为那时我们的注意力已从可感知世界转移开。', '副词: sensibly 名词: sensibleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quart', '[kwɔːrt]', 'n.夸脱（容量单位）', '1. There is a quart of milk left in the pail. 桶里还剩下一夸脱牛奶。 2. You cannot get a quart into a pint pot. 你无法把一夸脱的酒装进一品脱的瓶中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('display', '[dɪ\'spleɪ]', 'n.显示；陈列；炫耀 vt.显示；表现；夸示', '1. Let\'s display the figures and see what we have. 通过显示一下数字看看我们能看到什么。 2. The bottles of whisky on display are all dummies. 所陈列的威士忌酒都是假的。 3. There will be a display of bronze statuary in this museum next week. 下星期这个博物馆将举办一个青铜雕塑作品展览。 4. He made a display of his learning. 他夸耀自己有学问。 5. I have rarely seen her display any sign of emotion. 我难得见到她将喜怒形于色。', '过去式: displayed 过去分词: displayed 现在分词: displaying 第三人称单数: displays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pain', '[peɪn]', 'n.痛苦；疼痛；辛苦；烦人之人或事 v.使 ... 痛苦；痛苦；疼', '1. His leg was broken and he suffered great pain. 他的腿断了,遭受了巨大痛苦的折磨。 2. He has a pain in the knee. 他膝盖酸痛。 3. He spares no efforts to study English. 他不辞劳苦地学习英语。 4. She\'s been complaining again she\'s a real pain! 她又发牢骚了－－真烦人！ 5. She\'s pained by her son\'s conduct. 她对儿子的行为感到痛心。', '过去式: pained 过去分词: pained 现在分词: paining 第三人称单数: pains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('angel', '[\'eɪndʒl]', 'n.天使；天使般的人', '1. A stunt man needs to have a good guardian angel. 当特技替身演员的得有个守护天使来保佑。 2. No sin at all is the dream of the angel. 不犯错误，那是天使的梦想。 3. She is painting an angel with outspread wings. 她正在画一个张开翅膀的天使。 4. She is lovely -- as much so as an angel. 她可爱得像个天使。', '形容词: angelic 副词: angelically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bench', '[bentʃ]', 'n.长凳；工作台；法官', '1. This bench is made of elm. 这条长凳是榆木制的。 2. An old man sat on the park bench and fed the pigeon. 一位老人坐在公园的长凳上喂鸽子。 3. A young woman, of sullen aspect, was sitting alone on the bench. 一个面色忧郁的年轻女人独自坐在长凳上。 4. I\'m glad the new trainee is keen but I wish he\'d stop hanging around my bench and getting in my hair. 新来的受训者很敏捷，我很满意，不过我希望他别再我工作台周围闲荡，使我觉得烦恼。', '过去式: benched 过去分词: benched 现在分词: benching 第三人称单数: benches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rein', '[reɪn]', 'n.缰绳；驾驭；控制 vt.控制；驾驭 vi.驾驭', '1. He pulled at the reins. 他使劲拉住缰绳。 2. The horse responds to the slightest pull on the rein. 只要缰绳稍稍一拉，这匹马就有反应。 3. He gave rein to his imagination. 他纵情想像。 4. It\'s essential to keep a tight rein on public spending. 对公共开支严加控制极为重要。 5. We need to rein back public spending. 我们需要严格控制公共开销。 6. This horse reins well. 这匹马易于驾驭。', '过去式: reined 过去分词: reined 现在分词: reining 第三人称单数: reins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exhaust', '[ɪɡ\'zɔːst]', 'v.使筋疲力尽；耗尽；详尽论述 n.排气装置；废气', '1. Caring for young children can exhaust you physically and mentally. 照顾小孩子会使你身心疲惫。 2. The expedition was forced to turn back when it exhausted its food supply. 没有了食物,这个探险队不得不返航。 3. He failed to exhaust this subject. 他没能对这个题作详尽无遗的论述。 4. The car needs a new exhaust. 这辆车需要换一个新的排气管。', '形容词: exhaustible 副词: exhaustedly 名词: exhauster 过去式: exhausted 过去分词: exhausted 现在分词: exhausting 第三人称单数: exhausts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exotic', '[ɪɡ\'zɑːtɪk]', 'adj.外来的；异国的；奇异的；脱衣舞的', '1. Exotic pets are the in thing right now. 外国宠物眼下很时髦。 2. The film retains much of the book\'s exotic flavour. 这部电影保存了原著的许多异国情调。 3. The taste of this exotic dish puts me off. 这道异国菜肴的味道令我望而却步。 4. The exotic atmosphere will fascinate you. 这里的异国情调风格将会把您深深地迷住。', '副词: exotically 名词: exoticness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soar', '[sɔːr]', 'vi.翱翔；高飞；猛增；高涨；高耸 n.翱翔；高飞', '1. The eagle can soar without flapping their wings. 老鹰无需振翼就能翱翔。 2. Food prices soar during the cold weather. 这个寒冷的冬季食品价格猛涨。 3. Air pollution will soon soar above safety levels. 空气污染会很快突破安全标准。 4. Finally, the river continued to soar, the priest was merciless floods drowned. 最后，河水继续高涨，神父被无情的洪水淹死了。 5. The soar of trade brings big benefits to the two countries. 贸易的剧增给两国带来了极大的好处。', '副词: soaringly 名词: soarer 过去式: soared 过去分词: soared 现在分词: soaring 第三人称单数: soars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clip', '[klɪp]', 'vt.夹住 v.剪短 v.疾驰；猛击 n.夹子；弹夹；回形针；钳 n.修剪；(羊毛的)剪下量；(被剪下的)东西', '1. Do you clip those ear-rings on/Do those ear-rings clip on 你的[这种]耳环是夹上去的吗? 2. There was a cheque clipped to the back of the letter. 在信背面夹着一张支票。 3. The dog\'s fur was clipped short for the show. 为参加狗展狗的毛剪短了。 4. A horse is clipping down the road. 一匹马正沿路奔驰。 5. Winston stroked his nose gently with a paper clip. 温斯顿用一个纸夹子轻轻地擦着鼻子。 6. He gave the sheep a close clip. 他把羊的毛剪得很短。', '过去式: clipped 过去分词: clipped 现在分词: clipping 第三人称单数: clips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('permeate', '[\'pɜːrmieɪt]', 'v.弥漫；渗透；普及', '1. His subtle satisfaction seemed to permeate the space around them. 他难以捉摸的满足感好像弥漫在了他们的周围。 2. If your wine is still, pour it into the centre of the glass to let the bouquet permeate the vessel. 如果是无汽泡的酒，直接倒入杯子中央，使酒的香气充分散发，弥漫整个酒杯。 3. Water will permeate blotting paper. 水能渗透吸水纸。 4. Functional relationships permeate every part of science. 函数关系渗透自然科学的每个部分。', '形容词: permeant 名词: permeation 过去式: permeated 过去分词: permeated 现在分词: permeating 第三人称单数: permeates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tooth', '[tuːθ]', 'n.牙齿；齿状物；粗糙表面；嗜好 （复）teeth: 有效手段.', '1. This tooth is sensitive to cold. 这颗牙对冷过敏。 2. I was fitted an artificial tooth by the dentist. 牙医给我镶了颗假牙。 3. We should brush our teeth at least twice a day. 我们每天应该至少刷两次牙。 4. He bellowed with pain when the tooth was pulled out. 牙被拔掉时，他疼得大叫。 5. The law must be given more teeth if crime is to be properly controlled. 要想有效控制住犯罪活动，就得加强法制的威力。', '名词复数: teeth 过去式: toothed 过去分词: toothed 现在分词: toothing 第三人称单数: tooths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('staircase', '[\'sterkeɪs]', 'n.楼梯', '1. I hear someone coming down the staircase. 我听到有人下楼梯。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surprise', '[sər\'praɪz]', 'n.惊奇；惊喜；惊讶；突然 vt.使惊奇；使惊喜；突然袭击；惊讶地发现', '1. John turned around and looked at me in surprise. 约翰转过身来,惊奇地望着我。 2. It was a great surprise to learn of her marriage. 得知她结婚是一件十分令人惊喜的事。 3. I tried to conceal my surprise when she said she was only 22. 当她说她只有22岁时,我尽力掩饰自己的惊讶。 4. I must say the news came as a total surprise. 我得说这个消息来得太突然了。 5. The news greatly surprised them. 这消息使他们大为吃惊。', '形容词: surprising 副词: surprisingly 名词: surpriser');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beam', '[biːm]', 'vi.微笑；发光 vt.播送；发射；用梁支撑 n.桁条；光线；(光线的)束；(横)梁', '1. She beamed at me. 她对我微笑。 2. His face(He) is beaming with delight. 他高兴得笑容满面。 3. From a sky of untarnished blue the sun beamed down upon Beijing. 阳光透过万里碧空照耀着北京城。 4. Television began beaming the national nominating conventions into the homes of Americans. 电视开始向美国家庭播放总统候选人全国提名大会的情况。 5. A rotary table helps to optimize the beam incidence angle. 一张旋转的桌子有助于将光线影响之方式角最佳化。', '过去式: beamed 过去分词: beamed 现在分词: beaming 第三人称单数: beams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('building', '[\'bɪldɪŋ]', 'n.建筑物', '1. The heat had blistered the paint of the building. 酷热使建筑物上的油漆起了浮泡。 2. The building faces north. 这栋建筑物朝北。 3. The building does not conform to safety regulations. 这座建筑物不符合安全条例。 4. Houses and churches are buildings. 房子和教堂是建筑物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('explosive', '[ɪk\'sploʊsɪv]', 'adj.爆炸(性)的；引发争论的；大声的 n.炸药', '1. Hydrogen is highly explosive. 氢极易爆炸。 2. The most impressive volcanic phenomena are explosive eruptions. 最令人难忘的火山现象是爆炸喷发。 3. The question of race today is an explosive one. 种族问题在今天是一个会引起激烈争论的问题。 4. He bent double with explosive laughter. 他大笑得直不起腰来。 5. We carefully moved the explosive to another place. 我们谨慎地把炸药转移到了另一个地方。', '副词: explosively 名词: explosiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('muscular', '[\'mʌskjələr]', 'adj.肌肉的；肌肉发达的', '1. In order to climb hills, muscular power is another key trait. 为了爬坡，肌肉的力量是另一种关键特性。 2. Eucalyptus oil is good for easing muscular aches and pains. 桉树油可以很好地缓解肌肉的疼痛。 3. The rib cage is moderately sprung and extends back to a short and muscular loin. 肋骨适度撑起，向后延伸到短而肌肉发达的腰部。 4. Her gaze rested for a moment on the muscular neck,heavy corded,almost bull-like,bronzed by the sun,spilling over with rugged health and strength. 她的目光在那肌肉发达的脖子上停留了片刻，那脖子被太阳晒成了青铜色，筋位突出，洋溢着粗糙的健康与强力，几乎像公牛。', '副词: muscularly 名词: muscularity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('textbook', '[\'tekstbʊk]', 'n.课本；教科书', '1. Each student was issued with a textbook. 每个学生发了一本课本。 2. This textbook has twenty lessons. 这课本有二十课。 3. There is a glossary at the end of the textbook. 这本教科书后面有词汇表。 4. That old edition won\'t do for a textbook. 那一老版本作为教科书是不行的。', '形容词: textbookish');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('amend', '[ə\'mend]', 'vt.修正；改进', '1. They decided to amend the bill. 他们决定修正这条议案。 2. Please amend your copy of the contract accordingly. 请将你的合同文本作相应的修正。 3. Since you insist, I must amend the letter of credit. 既然你坚持，我就只好修改信用证。 4. I would advise you to amend your manners. 我劝你改正你的态度', '过去式: amended 过去分词: amended 现在分词: amending 第三人称单数: amends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('waterproof', '[\'wɔːtərpruːf]', 'adj. 防水的； 耐水的 n. 防水材料 （英）雨衣 vt. 使 ... 能防水', '1. He promised that it is waterproof. 他向我保证是防水的。 2. Marching rations are stored away in waterproof boxes. 行军干粮被存放在防水的盒子里。 3. Lanxi Ooston Waterpoof Materials Factory was set uo by a returning doctor wbo had been studying in Gremany.It produces the new-style building waterproof materials. 兰溪市诺西顿防水材料厂由留德博士回国创办，专业生产新型建筑防水材料。 4. Before a storm, sailors cover the hatches with waterproof material.Then they nail on battens to hold the hatch coverings firmly in place.This keeps rain and waves out of the ship. 在暴风雨之前，水手们用防水材料盖住舱口，然后用钉钉牢板条来把舱口的覆盖物很好的固定在位置上。 5. In lieu of carrying an umbrella, I wore a waterproof coat and cap. 我穿一件雨衣，戴一顶雨帽，就不用带雨伞了。 6. An umbrella should be waterproof. 雨伞应能防水。', '过去式: waterproofed 过去分词: waterproofed 现在分词: waterproofing 第三人称单数: waterproofs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('late', '[leɪt]', 'adj.迟的；晚的；末期的；最近的；已故的 adv.晚；迟', '1. I\'m afraid I may be a little late. 恐怕我可能稍晚一点。 2. The train was 10 minutes late. 火车晚点了10 分钟。 3. This country was founded in the late eighteenth century. 这个国家是在18世纪末期建立的。 4. Tell me about his late illness. 告诉我他最近的病况。 5. We went to bed late. 我们很晚才上床。', '比较级: later 最高级: latest 名词: lateness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sanction', '[\'sæŋkʃn]', 'n.批准；约束力；处罚 vt.批准；支持', '1. The minister can only act in this matter with the sanction of Parliament. 部长只有得到国会批准才能就此事采取行动。 2. The book was translated without the sanction of the author. 这本书未经作者许可就给翻译了。 3. Western nations imposed tough sanctions on the country. 西方各国对这个国家实行了严厉制裁。 4. The church would not sanction the king\'s second marriage. 教会不会批准国王第二次结婚。', '过去式: sanctioned 过去分词: sanctioned 现在分词: sanctioning 第三人称单数: sanctions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skin', '[skɪn]', 'n.皮肤；外皮；皮囊 n.惊讶；生气 vt.剥皮；削皮；贴皮；蹭破皮；<俚>击败', '1. He had brown skin. 他的皮肤是棕色的 2. When he fell he just broke the skin. 当他跌倒时，他只擦破皮肤。 3. She peeled off the skin of a banana for the child. 她替孩子剥掉香蕉皮。 4. I nearly jumped out of my skin when a hand grabbed me in the dark. 黑暗中有一只手把我抓住，可真把我吓了一大跳。 5. David is skinning onions in the kitchen. 大卫在厨房里剥洋葱皮。', '形容词: skinless 过去式: skinned 过去分词: skinned 现在分词: skinning 第三人称单数: skins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pirate', '[\'paɪrət]', 'n.海盗；盗版者 v.盗版；抢劫；剽窃', '1. The sailor suddenly saw a pirate jumping onto the deck. 那水手忽然看到一名海盗跳上了甲板。 2. Those software pirates have made a great fortune. 这些软件的盗版者发了大财。 3. We will immediately call the police once we find our CDs being pirated. 一旦发现我们的唱片被盗版,我们会立即报警。 4. A gang of bandits pirated the cargo ship. 一帮土匪抢劫了那艘货船。', '形容词: piratic 副词: piratically 过去式: pirated 过去分词: pirated 现在分词: pirating 第三人称单数: pirates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sparkle', '[\'spɑːrkl]', 'n.闪耀；火花 v.闪耀；冒火花', '1. There was a sparkle of excitement in her eyes. 她眼里闪耀着激动的光芒。 2. A single sparkle shone at first, like a first sparked wispling. 一个火花先闪烁了起来，如同一个首次闪亮的幽光般。 3. The stars sparkle in the dark sky. 夜晚的天空上星星闪闪发光。', '过去式: sparkled 过去分词: sparkled 现在分词: sparkling 第三人称单数: sparkles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('friendship', '[\'frendʃɪp]', 'n.友谊；友好', '1. Take this ring as a pledge of our friendship. 请接受这个戒指作为我们友谊的信物。 2. Real friendship is more valuable than money. 真正的友谊比金钱更宝贵。 3. He swore eternal friendship with me. 他发誓和我永远友好。 4. He rebuffed all my offers of friendship. 他拒绝了我的一切友好表示。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rare', '[rer]', 'adj.罕见的；珍贵的；煎得嫩的', '1. It is rare to find such a genius nowadays. 这样的天才现在很少见。 2. It was in the days when motorcars were rare. 那是在汽车还罕见的时代。 3. He\'s devoted his whole life to the protection of the rare animals. 他终生献身于珍稀动物的保护。 4. Those rare books are shelved in the East Library. 那些珍贵的书籍都放在图书馆东馆的架子上。', '比较级: rarer 最高级: rarest 名词: rareness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gorgeous', '[\'ɡɔːrdʒəs]', 'adj.华丽的；灿烂的；极好的', '1. The gorgeous costume added to the brilliance of the dance. 华丽的服装使舞蹈更加光彩夺目。 2. In the evening the rosy clouds were gorgeous. 傍晚的云霞绚丽多彩。 3. The garden is gorgeous with peonies. 花园里盛开着绚丽的牡丹花。 4. What a gorgeous day! 多美好的一天啊!', '副词: gorgeously 名词: gorgeousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('track', '[træk]', 'n.轨道；跑道；踪迹；小路；乐曲 v.追踪；跟踪', '1. The tram is being switched on to another track . 电车正被移至另外一条轨道上。 2. The cyclist went at full sail along the track. 自行车手沿着跑道全速前进。 3. I quickly lose her track in the crowd. 我在人群中失去了她的踪迹。 4. A track runs across the field to his house. 一条小路穿过原野通到他的家。 5. It\'s difficult to track an animal right after rain. 刚下完雨后要追踪猎物是很困难的。', '形容词: trackable 名词: tracker 过去式: tracked 过去分词: tracked 现在分词: tracking 第三人称单数: tracks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('housing', '[\'haʊzɪŋ]', 'n.房屋；外壳；外套；外罩；住宅；卡箍；遮盖物；(芯片的)封装', '1. Many immigrants here are living in bad housing. 这儿有许多移民住在破败的房屋里。 2. He is assisted by staff in the Housing Bureau. 他从房屋局工作人员那得到了协助。 3. Install bulbs and sockets in the lamp housing. 安装灯泡和插座于灯外壳上。 4. We are financing for the housing project. 我们在为住宅计划筹措资金。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('level', '[\'levl]', 'n.数量；等级；水平；水平线 adj.平的；等高的 v.弄平；夷平；对准 adv.<废>水平地', '1. Levels of unemployment vary from region to region. 失业情形各地不同. 2. We each perceive the outside world differently according to our level. 我们每个人对外在世界的感觉,因个人等级不同而有所差异。 3. We must increase production levels. 我们必须提高生产水平。 4. The top of this mountain is three kilometers above the sea level. 这座山的山顶海拔三千米高。 5. A football field should be level. 足球场地应该平坦。 6. We need a mechanical digger to level the ground. 我们需要一台挖掘机来平整土地。', '副词: levelly 名词: levelness 过去式: leveled/levelled 过去分词: leveled/levelled 现在分词: leveling/levelling 第三人称单数: levels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anyhow', '[\'enihaʊ]', 'adv.无论如何；不管怎样', '1. Anyhow,Spring will return to us. 春，无论如何也会回到人间。 2. Anyhow I must finish this job today. 无论如何，我今天要完成这件事。 3. Anyhow, don\'t worry yourself now about it. 不管怎样，现在不要为这事烦恼了。 4. But anyhow they are engaged to be married. 但是不管怎样他们订婚了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pie', '[paɪ]', 'n.馅饼；饼图 n.喜鹊；爱说话的人(=magpie)', '1. That pie tastes good. 那个馅饼味道不错。 2. Help yourself to this apple pie. 请吃点苹果馅饼。 3. Pie and doughnut charts do not have axes. 饼图和圆环图没有轴。 4. She can talk for the whole day, just like a pie. 她整天说话,像只喜鹊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('applicable', '[ə\'plɪkəbl]', 'adj.合适的；适用的；可应用的', '1. Western notions of human rights are not necessarily applicable in other societies. 西方的人权观念不一定适合其他社会。 2. This section of the law is applicable only to corporations. 这部分法律只适用于公司。 3. This part of the form is not applicable to foreign students. 表格中的这一部分不适用於外国学生. 4. Above rate applicable until further notice. 除非另有通知，上述运费率适用。', '副词: applicably 名词: applicability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('helpful', '[\'helpfl]', 'adj.有帮助的；有用的', '1. You are very helpful. 您真帮了我的大忙。 2. These things are helpful for my life. 而且对我的生活是有帮助的。 3. These tactics are unlikely to be helpful to you. 这种方法对你未必有用。 4. The experience in army is helpful to him. 他从军的经历对他很有用。', '副词: helpfully 名词: helpfulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('its', '[ɪts]', 'pron.（it的所有格)它的', '1. The word here is used in its figurative sense. 此词在这儿取的是它的比喻意义。 2. He felt the cloth to see its quality. 他摸摸布看它的品质。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('physics', '[\'fɪzɪks]', 'n.物理学', '1. He does well in physics. 他的物理学得很好。 2. I prefer chemistry to physics. 我喜欢化学甚于物理。 3. She majored in maths and physics at university. 她在大学期间主修数学和物理。 4. He has got brilliant achievements in the field of physics. 他在物理学方面已经取得了卓越的成就。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flesh', '[fleʃ]', 'n.肉；肉体；人类 v.充实；变胖', '1. The knife cut the flesh of his arm. 小刀把他胳膊上的肉割破了。 2. The pain was almost more than flesh could take. 疼痛几乎使肉体受不了。 3. We are made from flesh and soul. 我们是肉体与灵魂结合的产物。 4. His life was devoted to the pleasure of the flesh. 他一生贪图肉体上的舒适享受。 5. Examples were used to flesh out the skeleton of the argument. 通过例证使干巴巴的论点充实起来。', '形容词: fleshless 过去式: fleshed 过去分词: fleshed 现在分词: fleshing 第三人称单数: fleshes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('really', '[\'riːəli]', 'adv.实在；真正地；事实上', '1. It\'s really cold today. 今天可真冷。 2. It\'s really too bad that the teacher couldn\'t find someone to substitute for her when she was sick. 她生病时,老师找不到人代替她,实在太遗憾了。 3. Go ahead. Do whatever you really love. 去吧,去做你真正喜爱的事。 4. After the shock of their electoral defeat, the party really began to pull together. 该党在受到选举失败的打击之后，才真正地团结起来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('classroom', '[\'klæsruːm]', 'n.教室；课堂', '1. The classroom was crammed with students. 教室里挤满了学生。 2. Teachers rule in classroom teaching. 在课堂教学中教师占主导地位。 3. Don\'t confine your study only to the classroom. 不要把自己的学习只局限于课堂。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('notice', '[\'noʊtɪs]', 'vt.注意；留心；通知 n.通知；注意；布告', '1. He walked so fast that he didn\'t notice his wife. 他走得太快了,连他夫人都没注意到。 2. I notice you aren\'t quite convinced. 我感到你还不太相信。 3. As soon as your application is approved, I will personally notice you. 核发登记证时我会通知您。 4. Information maybe revised without prior notice. 数据如有修改,恕不另行通知。', '过去式: noticed 过去分词: noticed 现在分词: noticing 第三人称单数: notices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hardship', '[\'hɑːrdʃɪp]', 'n.艰难；困苦', '1. We are ready to face any hardship. 我们准备好了面对任何艰难。 2. He will not shrink from any hardship. 他不会因任何艰难而畏缩。 3. A strong man will bear hardship without complaining. 一个坚强的人会忍受困苦而不抱怨。 4. His health broke after years of hardship. 多年的困苦生活使他的身体垮了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('raid', '[reɪd]', 'n.突然袭击；突击搜捕；劫掠；集体抛售 v.劫掠；攫取；突击搜捕；袭击', '1. We launched a bombing raid on enemy bases. 我们对敌方基地实施了突然袭击。 2. The raid was purely retaliatory. 这次袭击完全是报复性的。 3. Police made a lightning raid on the house. 警方突然查抄了那座房子。 4. They were arrested during a dawn raid. 在一次清晨的突击搜查中，他们都被捕了。 5. They promise they will never raid tourist. 他们保证再也不抢劫游客。', '名词: raider 过去式: raided 过去分词: raided 现在分词: raiding 第三人称单数: raids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exam', '[ɪɡ\'zæm]', 'n.考试', '1. He repeatedly fails to pass the exam. 他考了多次都不及格。 2. I was really in a fog after the exam. 考完试后，我真的感到稀里糊涂。 3. He didn\'t pass the exam, but it was a good attempt. 他虽然没有通过考试，但他做了很大的努力。 4. She crammed for her history exam. 她死记硬背以应付历史考试。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tissue', '[\'tɪʃuː]', 'n.纸巾；薄绢；(生物的)组织；织物', '1. She gave us a box of tissues. 她递给我们一盒纸巾。 2. She wiped off the sweat from her face with a piece of facial tissue. 她用一张面巾纸擦掉脸上的汗水。 3. On her head was a tiny cap of silver tissue. 她头上戴着一顶银丝小帽。 4. Human tissue is made up of cells. 人体的组织是由细胞构成的。', '形容词: tissuey');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relative', '[\'relətɪv]', 'adj.相对的；比较的；相关的 n.亲戚；[语]关系词', '1. Motion is absolute while stagnation is relative. 运动是绝对的,而静止是相对的。 2. They are now living in relative comfort. 他们现在过着比较安逸的生活。 3. Relative to the size, the city is sparsely populated. 与其面积相比, 这个城市的人口是稀少的。 4. The teacher asked me some questions relative to my paper. 老师问了我一些和我的论文有关的问题。 5. He showed such concern that people took him to be a relative. 他很关心别人，因而大家都把他当作亲人。', '名词: relativeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glow', '[ɡloʊ]', 'n.光辉；热情；赤热 vi.发红光；红光焕发', '1. There is a glow of health in his face. 他的脸容光焕发。 2. There midnight\'s all a glimmer and noon (is) a purple glow. 那儿午夜浮光微摇，中午紫光争耀。 3. The sunset glow is very beautiful. 太阳的余辉非常美丽。 4. His face took on an affectionate glow. 他的脸上洋溢着热情的红光。 5. All fireflies glow with about the same brightness. 所有的萤火虫闪耀着差不多相同的光亮。', '过去式: glowed 过去分词: glowed 现在分词: glowing 第三人称单数: glows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('living', '[\'lɪvɪŋ]', 'adj.活着的；生动的 n.生活；生计 动词live的现在分词.', '1. I\'ll tell you a secret that I have never told a living soul. 我要告诉你一个我从未告诉过任何人的秘密。 2. He was the greatest living novelist in England. 他是英国活着的最伟大的小说家。 3. The wilderness is a living museum of natural history. 这片荒野是一座活生生的自然历史博物馆。 4. The judge advised him to amend his way of living. 法官劝告他改变生活方式。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sky', '[skaɪ]', 'n.天空；天气；天国 v.<英>把...投向空中；将…高挂', '1. He stared up at the stars twinkling in the sky above him. 他抬眼凝视着头顶上方星光闪烁的天空。 2. The sky slowly changed from blue to red. 天空慢慢由蓝色变为红色。 3. A cloud is a mass of vapor in the sky. 云是天空中的水汽团。 4. Threatening skies portend a storm. 诡异的天气预示有暴风雨来临。 5. It is silly of him to take a wild swipe at the ball and sky it mile over the bar. 他真傻，猛踢足球，把它高高地踢过了球门。', '名词复数: skies 过去式: skied 过去分词: skied 现在分词: skying 第三人称单数: skies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Catholic', '[\'kæθlɪk]', 'adj.天主教的；(catholic)普遍的；广泛的 n.天主教徒', '1. Anselm\'s theology is not Catholic faith. 安塞姆的神学并不是天主教的信念。 2. The atom bomb is of catholic concern. 原子弹受到普遍的关注。 3. As a young person he had more catholic tastes than he does now. 他在年轻时兴趣比现在广泛得多。 4. Leonardo da Vinci was a catholic genius who excelled in almost everything he did. 达文西是一个广泛的天才,他做的很多事也得到成功。 5. He was a Catholic but didn\'t practise his religion. 他那时是天主教徒，但并不实践信仰。', '副词: catholically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('of', '[əv]', 'prep.关于；... 的（表所属）；出身于；由于', '1. I have heard of him. 我听说过他。 2. This is a photograph of my dog. 这是一张我的狗的照片。 3. He is a friend of my father. 他是我父亲的朋友。 4. He is a Prime Minister of working class origin. 他是一位工人出身的总理。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('leading', '[\'liːdɪŋ]', 'adj.领导的；指导的；主要的；在前的', '1. He is a leading cadre. 他是个领导干部。 2. She tried to beat up some support for the campaign she was leading. 她力求赢得人们对她所领导的运动的支持。 3. This old man is a leading authority on wheat diseases. 这位老人是小麦病虫害方面的权威。 4. The director cast her in a leading part when she was a young unknown of 16. 当她还是一个十六岁的无名少女时，导演选中她演主角。', '副词: leadingly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ultraviolet', '[ˌʌltrə\'vaɪələt]', 'adj.紫外线的 n.紫外线', '1. The ozone layer shields the earth from the sun\'s ultraviolet rays. 臭氧层保护地球不受太阳紫外线的辐射。 2. A suncream provides adequate protection against harmful ultraviolet rays. 使用防晒霜可以保护皮肤不受紫外线的伤害。 3. Ultraviolet rays can penetrate through clouds. 紫外线可以穿透云层。 4. What are infrared and ultraviolet rays? 什么是红外线和紫外线？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('semester', '[sɪ\'mestər]', 'n.学期', '1. His writing has improved greatly in this semester. 这学期他的写作有了很大进步。 2. This semester will be my last one in this university. 这个学期将是我在这所大学的最后一学期了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hopeful', '[\'hoʊpfl]', 'adj.有希望的', '1. I\'m hopeful that they\'ll fulfil the task on time. 他们会按时完成任务，对这一点，我是抱有希望的。 2. I am very hopeful that we will be able to reach an agreement. 大家都作一点让步，那么达成协议很有希望的。', '名词: hopefulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('logic', '[\'lɑːdʒɪk]', 'n.逻辑；逻辑学；条理性；推理', '1. I didn\'t follow her logic. 我不理解她的逻辑。 2. His thinking goes against all logic. 他的思维完全不合逻辑。 3. Socrates laid the foundations of logic. 苏格拉底奠定了逻辑学的基础。 4. Your friend doesn\'t seem to be controlled by logic. 你那位朋友好像没有逻辑性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yell', '[jel]', 'v.大叫 n.大喊', '1. Don\'t yell at me! 别对我大喊大叫！ 2. You don\'t have to yell; I can hear you. 你用不著喊，我听得见。 3. She yelled out at her mischievous child. 她对她淘气的孩子大喊大叫。 4. We yelled our good-byes as the bus left. 汽车离开时我们大喊再见。 5. She let out a yell and ran home. 她尖叫了一声跑回了家。', '名词: yeller 过去式: yelled 过去分词: yelled 现在分词: yelling 第三人称单数: yells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('war', '[wɔːr]', 'n.战争；斗争 v.作战；斗争', '1. The hope of a short war went glimmering. 战争无望在短期内结束。 2. A series of provocations led up to the border war. 一系列的挑衅事件导致了边境战争的发生。 3. The army was disbanded when the war came to an end. 战争结束时，军队即被解散。 4. They are waging a war against crime. 他们正在展开一场反对犯罪的斗争。', '过去式: warred 过去分词: warred 现在分词: warring 第三人称单数: wars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poison', '[\'pɔɪzn]', 'n.毒药；毒害；败坏道德之事 vt.毒害；摧毁；中毒 adj.有毒的；危险的', '1. We detected traces of the poison in her food. 我们在她的食物里发现了微量毒药。 2. He tried to kill himself by taking poison. 他曾试图服毒自杀。 3. Some people say that selfishness is a poison in our society. 有些人说自私是我们社会的一害。 4. Someone tried to poison our dog. 有人想毒杀我们的狗。 5. Nonetheless, an Argentine pathologist who has studied diethylene glycol poisonings helped develop a test for the poison in exhumed bodies. 尽管如此，来自于阿根廷的病原学家仍然在掘出的尸体中检测出有毒的甘油。', '名词: poisoner 过去式: poisoned 过去分词: poisoned 现在分词: poisoning 第三人称单数: poisons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('daily', '[\'deɪli]', 'adj.每日的；日常的 adv.每日；天天 n.日报 (复)dailies：工作样片.', '1. He writes for the daily newspaper. 他为那家日报撰稿。 2. As a result, daily output has doubled. 结果日产量翻了一番。 3. Daily practice is the trick in learning a foreign language. 每天练习是学会一门外语的诀窍。 4. I need a holiday as a relief from the daily grind. 我需要休假以摆脱单调的日常工作。 5. The bakery serves us with fresh bread daily. 面包店每天都给我们提供新鲜面包。 6. I like to read China Daily on my way home. 我喜欢在回家的途中阅读《中国日报》。', '名词: dailiness 名词复数: dailies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crew', '[kruː]', 'n.全体船员；全体乘务员；(一组)工作人员；划艇队员 v.当船员；当机务人员', '1. The ship set sail after all the crew came on board. 全体船员上船后，船就开了。 2. The crew abandoned the sinking ship. 全体船员离开了正在下沉的船。 3. The plane crashed, killing all its passengers and crew. 飞机失事了，所有乘客和机组人员都遇难了。 4. The captain piped the crew down after work. 船长吹哨让全体船员下班。', '过去式: crewed 过去分词: crewed 现在分词: crewing 第三人称单数: crews');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('proceeding', '[prə\'siːdɪŋ]', 'n.行动；诉讼程序；会议记录', '1. I swear that, from now on, I will keep on with the proceeding. 我宣誓,从今往后,我要不断行动。 2. The manager is thinking about what the best way of proceeding is. 经理正在考虑最好采取什麽方式继续下去。 3. The intern students became familiar with the entire course of a judicial proceeding. 实习生逐渐熟悉诉讼程序司法程序的全过程。 4. The proceedings were published in the newspaper. 会议记录已在报上公布。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('industrialize', '[ɪn\'dʌstriəlaɪz]', 'v.(使)工业化 =industrialise(英).', '1. Many townships in the coastal area have begin to industrialize. 沿海地区的许多乡镇已开始工业化。 2. We have to make our every effort to industrialize our country. 我们应该尽最大的努力，使我们的国家工业化。', '名词: industrialization 过去式: industrialized 过去分词: industrialized 现在分词: industrializing 第三人称单数: industrializes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beat', '[biːt]', 'v.打；打败；跳动；敲打；战胜 n.拍子；敲打；心跳声 adj.精疲力尽的', '1. His father beat the disobedient boy. 他的父亲打那个不听话的男孩。 2. If we don\'t prepare for the speech contest, they will beat us. 如果这场演讲比赛我们不做好准备的话,他们就会打败我们。 3. He\'s alive；his heart is still beating. 他还活著－－心脏还在跳。 4. They beat drums to cheer up the players. 他们擂鼓给运动员加油。 5. Every member of the band must follow the beat. 乐队的每个成员都必须跟着拍子演奏。 6. I am completely beat. 我累极了。', '过去式: beat 过去分词: beaten/beat 现在分词: beating 第三人称单数: beats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pour', '[pɔːr]', 'v.不断流动；倒；倾泻；蜂涌而来 n.倾泻', '1. Blood was pouring from the wound. 血从伤口中流出。 2. Although I poured it carefully, I spilt some of the oil. 虽然我倒油时很小心，但还是洒了一些。 3. She watched the rain pouring down the windows. 她注视著顺著窗户往下流的大雨。 4. The fans poured out of the stadium cheering wildly. 体育爱好者们欣喜若狂地从体育场中蜂涌而出。 5. Into the new work she was going to pour all her thoughts and feelings, her vital life episodes, her bitter sweet experiences. 她要把自己一生几个重要时期的经历和感受都熔入笔端倾泻在新作中。', '名词: pourer 过去式: poured 过去分词: poured 现在分词: pouring 第三人称单数: pours');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wear', '[wer]', 'v.磨损；穿戴；使疲劳 n.磨损；穿着；耐久性', '1. The inscription on the stone had worn away. 刻在石头上的文字已磨损了。 2. Machines soon wear out under rough usage. 机器如果使用不仔细, 很快就会磨损。 3. It was a freak of mine to wear pink pajamas. 穿上粉红色睡衣是我一时的奇想。 4. All visitors to the site must wear safety helmet. 到工地的所有参观者必须带上安全帽。 5. The insurance policy does not cover damage caused by normal wear and tear. 保险单内容不包括正常使用所导致的损坏。', '名词: wearer 过去式: wore 过去分词: worn 现在分词: wearing 第三人称单数: wears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('easy', '[\'iːzi]', 'adj.容易的；轻松的；不费力的；舒适的；安逸的；轻微的；随和的；无约束的', '1. It\'s not easy to rid oneself of a habit. 要改掉一个习惯是不容易的。 2. Her movements were easy and graceful. 她的动作轻松而优雅。 3. It was not easy for me to get the rusty nail out. 我好不容易才拔出这颗生锈的钉子。 4. He has stopped working and leads a very easy life now. 他现在不做事了,过着很舒服的日子。', '比较级: easier 最高级: easiest 名词: easiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gallery', '[\'ɡæləri]', 'n.美术馆；画廊；顶层楼座；走廊', '1. The gallery has a show of French oil painting. 这个美术馆在展出法国油画。 2. She is a frequent visitor to the gallery. 她经常参观这个美术馆。 3. The gallery is a treasure trove of medieval art. 这个画廊是中世纪艺术的宝库。 4. There\'s a new picture show at the gallery tomorrow. 明天在画廊有个新画展。', '形容词: galleried 名词复数: galleries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('simultaneous', '[ˌsaɪml\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.同时发生的；同步的', '1. The explosion was timed to be simultaneous with the plane\'s take-off. 爆炸的时间定在飞机起飞的时刻。 2. The simultaneous demonstrations are held in London and New York. 在伦敦和纽约同时举行示威游行。 3. There were several simultaneous attacks by the rebels. 反叛者同时发动了几起攻击。 4. Her work as a simultaneous translator requires strong powers of concentration. 作为同步翻译员，她的工作需要极大的专注力。', '副词: simultaneously 名词: simultaneousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('noise', '[nɔɪz]', 'n.噪声；喧闹声；响声 vt.谣传 vi.大声说话；发出噪音', '1. The loud noise from the nearby factory chafed him. 附近工厂的噪声使他烦燥。 2. The dog perked its ears at the noise. 一听到噪声，狗就竖起了耳朵 3. There is so much noise in this restaurant; I can hardly hear you talking. 这个餐厅里太嘈杂了，我几乎听不到你说话。 4. A loud noise from the street diverted my attention. 街上一阵喧闹声转移了我的注意力。 5. It was noised abroad that his company had gone bankrupt. 外面谣传他的公司已破产。 6. There was a ceaseless noise of machinery. 机器不停地发出噪音。', '过去式: noised 过去分词: noised 现在分词: noising 第三人称单数: noises 形容词: noisy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lunar', '[\'luːnər]', 'adj.月亮的；阴历的；银的', '1. The astronauts piloted their craft down to the lunar surface. 宇航员驾驶宇宙飞船在月球表面降落。 2. Lunar eclipse occur when the earth\'s shadow fall on the moon. 地球的影子落在月球上时,就发生月蚀。 3. It was reported that there would be a lunar eclipse tomorrow evening. 据报道说，明天晚上有月食。 4. All traditional Chinese festivals are lunar calendar festivals. 中国的传统节日都是按照太阴历计算的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('periodical', '[ˌpɪri\'ɑːdɪkl]', 'n.期刊 adj.定期的', '1. The periodical is obtainable on the very first day of every month. 这本杂志每月一号出版。 2. She refereed for a periodical a few years ago. 几年前她为一期刊担任编审。 3. They have already put out a new periodical. 他们已经出版了一种新的期刊。 4. I should be glad if you could insert this article into your periodical. 如果能把这篇文章登在你的期刊上我将很高兴。 5. I expect regular periodical reports from you. 我期待你定期汇报。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seek', '[siːk]', 'vt.寻求；追求；试图 vi.寻找', '1. Tortured by fear, he decided to seek the aid of a psychiatrist. 他终日恐惧不安,决定寻求心理医生的帮助。 2. Many single people are seeking that special someone. 许多单身人士都在追求他们的唯一。 3. Some nations will seek the change of their energy supply sources to reduce emissions, or for other reasons. 为了减少碳排量,或是出于其他原因,一些国家试图改变他们的能源供应来源。 4. You seek all day and you find it, and then you realize that it is worthless. 你终日寻寻觅觅,找到了,之后却发现那根本不值得寻找。', '过去式: sought 过去分词: sought 现在分词: seeking 第三人称单数: seeks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pavement', '[\'peɪvmənt]', 'n.路面；人行道；铺石；铺路材料', '1. Two cars skidded on the icy pavement. 两辆汽车在结冰的路面上打滑。 2. The pavement was covered with dogs\' excrement. 便道上满是狗屎。 3. She is a pavement sweeper. 她是一个打扫人行道的清扫工人。 4. Tourists crowded the pavement. 游客把人行道挤得水泄不通。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ugly', '[\'ʌɡli]', 'adj.丑陋的；难看的；令人困窘的；令人不愉快的', '1. Toads have an ugly appearance but they are useful. 蟾蜍外表丑陋，但很有用。 2. You can\'t persuade me to buy this ugly vase! 你不能劝服我买这个丑陋的花瓶！ 3. His face was covered in ugly red blotches. 他脸上有许多难看的红色大斑点。 4. What an ugly mug! 多难看的脸！', '副词: uglily 比较级: uglier 最高级: ugliest 名词: ugliness 名词复数: uglies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('observe', '[əb\'zɜːrv]', 'v.观察；遵守；注意到；庆祝', '1. We have to observe carefully what\'s going on there. 我们必须仔细观察那里的动静。 2. He made a telescope through which he could observe the stars. 他做了个望远镜,用其观察星座。 3. All citizens should observe traffic rules. 每位公民都应该遵守交通规则。 4. We should observe the proprieties. 我们应该遵守礼节。', '副词: observingly 过去式: observed 过去分词: observed 现在分词: observing 第三人称单数: observes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('day', '[deɪ]', 'n.白天；一天；时代', '1. Owls sleep by day and work at night. 猫头鹰白天睡觉晚上工作。 2. There will be occasional showers during the day. 白天将偶有阵雨。 3. He is seldom at home during the day. 他白天很少在家。 4. You can see stars by night, but not by day. 你在夜晚可以看到星星，白天却看不到。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ambassador', '[æm\'bæsədər]', 'n.大使；代表', '1. He was appointed ambassador to the United States. 他被任命为驻美国大使。 2. He never failed to send the ambassador a report each week. 他每个礼拜必送报告给大使。 3. The ambassador expects that his next posting will be (to) Paris. 那位大使预期他下次派驻巴黎。 4. He is seen by the black nation at the U.N. as an ambassador for blackness. 他被参加联合国的黑人国家看作黑人民族自豪感的代表。', '形容词: ambassadorial 名词: ambassadorship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('displace', '[dɪs\'pleɪs]', 'v.取代；移置；替换', '1. Weeds tend to displace other plants. 杂草越来越多，有取代其他植物之势。 2. Moderates have displaced the extremists on the committee. 在委员会中，稳健派人士取代了激进派人士。 3. Please don\'t displace my dictionaries. 请别动我的词典。 4. The indigenous population was soon displaced by the settlers. 没过多久，外来移民就把当地人赶出了家园。', '形容词: displaceable 名词: displacer 过去式: displaced 过去分词: displaced 现在分词: displacing 第三人称单数: displaces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tariff', '[\'tærɪf]', 'n.关税；价目表 vt.交关税', '1. Tariff barriers crimped the flow of imports. 关税障碍妨碍了进囗货的流入。 2. The government decided to impose a protective tariff on foreign cars. 政府决定对进口汽车征收保护税。 3. A copy of tariff is placed in each room of the hotel. 旅馆的每一个房间都有一份价目表。', '过去式: tariffed 过去分词: tariffed 现在分词: tariffing 第三人称单数: tariffs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('necessity', '[nə\'sesəti]', 'n.需要；必需品；必然', '1. Necessity is the mother of invention. 需要是发明之母。 2. Want and necessity break faiths and oaths. 匮乏和需要可以打破信仰和誓言。 3. Water is of vital necessity in the desert. 在沙漠地区水是维持生命的必需品。 4. Food is a necessity, but wine is an extravagance. 食物是必需品,而酒则是奢侈品。', '名词复数: necessities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coil', '[kɔɪl]', 'n.卷；圈；线圈 v.盘绕；卷成圈', '1. He passed me a coil of thread. 他递给我一卷线。 2. The birds are entangled in the coil of a net. 鸟被缠在网圈里了。 3. The burnt coil should be renewed. 烧穿的线圈应换新的。 4. This is a double induction coil. 这是一对感应线圈。 5. The snake coiled itself around the tree. 蛇盘绕在树上。', '名词: coiler 过去式: coiled 过去分词: coiled 现在分词: coiling 第三人称单数: coils');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loud', '[laʊd]', 'adj.大声的；吵闹的；引人注目的 adv.大声地；响亮地', '1. I gave a loud yawn, but he just kept on talking. 我大声打了个呵欠，可他还是不停地讲下去。 2. He cleared his nose with a loud sniff. 他大声吸气清了清鼻子。 3. All of this loud music is driving me up the wall. 这吵闹的音乐快令我发疯了。 4. He put plug in his ear because the noise was too loud. 因为太吵闹了，他用耳塞堵住了耳朵。 5. Don\'t talk so loud. 别那么大声地说话。', '副词: loudly 比较级: louder 最高级: loudest 名词: loudness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appoint', '[ə\'pɔɪnt]', 'v.任命；委派；指定；约定', '1. The company decided to appoint a new treasurer. 公司决定任命一位新司库。 2. They appointed him chairman. 他们任命他为主席。 3. As a top manager, he should appoint none but people on their merit. 作为一位总经理，他应该任人为贤。 4. We must appoint a new teacher soon. 我们必须尽快委派一个新教师。', '过去式: appointed 过去分词: appointed 现在分词: appointing 第三人称单数: appoints');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tram', '[træm]', 'n.缆车；煤车；有轨电车 v.乘缆车；用煤车运；乘有轨电车', '1. A tram was just arriving at the hill foot. 一辆缆车刚到达山脚下。 2. If you go to Melbourne, you can travel by tram. 如果你要去墨尔本，你可以做有轨电车。 3. The tram is being switched on to another track. 电车正被移至另外一条轨道上。', '过去式: trammed 过去分词: trammed 现在分词: tramming 第三人称单数: trams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mine', '[maɪn]', 'pron.我的 n.矿；地雷；矿藏 v.采矿；用地雷炸', '1. He is a distant cousin of mine. 他是我的一位远房表亲。 2. The mine was closed owing to exhaustion. 这个煤矿因矿源枯竭而被关闭。 3. The ship\'s bow was blown off by a mine. 船头给一枚水雷炸掉了。 4. A good encyclopaedia is a mine of information. 一部好的百科全书是一座知识宝库。 5. Peopel still mine for coal in this area. 人们还在这个地区开采煤矿。', '过去式: mined 过去分词: mined 现在分词: mining 第三人称单数: mines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thumb', '[θʌm]', 'n.拇指 v.翻阅；示意要求搭车', '1. Don\'t suck your thumb; it\'s so dirty. 别舔手指头，太脏了。 2. He caught his thumb in the door. 他的拇指让门夹了。 3. He thumbed through the address book looking for the number. 他翻阅地址簿，寻找号码。 4. You ought to thumb through this art book sometime. 你什么时候应该浏览一下这本美术书。', '过去式: thumbed 过去分词: thumbed 现在分词: thumbing 第三人称单数: thumbs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weight', '[weɪt]', 'n.重量；体重；重任；重要 vt.使 ... 负重；使倾斜', '1. The pillars have to support the weight of the roof. 这些柱子须承受屋顶的重量。 2. He gained some weight recently. 近来，他的体重增加了。 3. He has put on weight since I last saw him. 自从我上次见到他以来，他又长胖了。 4. The full weight of decision-making falls on her. 决策的重任全落在她的肩上了。 5. The true giants weight nearly a ton 这个真正的巨人的重量约达一吨', '过去式: weighted 过去分词: weighted 现在分词: weighting 第三人称单数: weights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('custom', '[\'kʌstəm]', 'n.习惯；风俗；惯例 （复）Customs: 海关；关税 adj.定做的；定制的', '1. The custom has now become a rule. 那种习惯现已变为成规。 2. It is my custom to go for a walk before breakfast. 早餐前出去散散步是我的习惯。 3. Custom rules the law. [谚]风俗左右法律。 4. The custom prevails over the whole area. 这风俗存在于这整个地区。 5. It took us only a few minutes to get through the Customs. 我们的海关检查只花了几分钟时间。 6. Please enter a name for the custom controller. 请输入自定义控制器的名称。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('growth', '[ɡroʊθ]', 'n.【U】增长；生长；发展；种植 n.【C】生长物；【医】瘤;赘生物', '1. Their growth rate is quite slow, but continuous. 其增长速度是相当缓慢,但持续。 2. We are entering a period of rapid population growth. 我们正在进入人类快速增长的时期。 3. Lack of demand will slow (down) our economic growth. 市场需求低就要拖慢我们的经济增长速度。 4. Cold weather retards the growth of the crops. 寒冷的天气妨碍了庄稼生长。 5. The abandoned garden was left to a wanton growth of weeds. 荒园里杂草丛生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oxide', '[\'ɑːksaɪd]', 'n.氧化物', '1. The nitride on oxide layers remains intact. 氧化物表层上面的氮化物保持原状不动。 2. Oxide is usually seen in our daily life. 在我们的日常生活中氧化物很常见。', '形容词: oxidic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('full', '[fʊl]', 'adj.满的；充满的；完全的 n.全部；极点 adv.非常；直接地 vt.使衣服宽松；增厚', '1. Hotels are often full in season 在度假旺季,旅馆经常客满。 2. He gave a boring speech full of stale jokes. 他的发言很乏味,满是陈腐的笑话。 3. The bottle is full of water. 瓶子里装满了水。 4. The roses are in full bloom. 玫瑰花盛开了。 5. Sign your name in full. 签下你的全名。 6. They knew full well that he wouldn\'t keep his promise. 他们很清楚地知道他不会遵守诺言。', '比较级: fuller 最高级: fullest 名词: fullness 过去式: fulled 过去分词: fulled 现在分词: fulling 第三人称单数: fulls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('muscle', '[\'mʌsl]', 'n.肌肉 v.硬挤；变硬实', '1. He strained his muscle in the match. 他在那次比赛中拉伤了肌肉。 2. The contraction of muscle is a reaction of the body. 肌肉的收缩是人体的一种反应。 3. He tried to muscle into the club. 他企图强行加入那个俱乐部。 4. Our competitors have been trying to muscle in for some years . 几年来，我们的竞争对手一直试图夺取利益。', '形容词: muscly 过去式: muscled 过去分词: muscled 现在分词: muscling 第三人称单数: muscles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shepherd', '[\'ʃepərd]', 'n.牧羊者；牧师；指导者 v.牧羊；照看；引领', '1. The shepherd set out to look for the sheep that had wandered away. 牧羊人出发去找走失的羊。 2. The poor boy was hired as a shepherd when he was only ten. 这个贫穷的小男孩在他十岁的时候就被雇为羊倌。 3. Born into a shepherd family, he is inclined to live a modest life. 他出身于一个牧师家庭，喜欢生活俭朴。 4. The shepherd and his dog gathered in the sheep. 牧羊人和牧羊狗把羊群赶到一块。', '过去式: shepherded 过去分词: shepherded 现在分词: shepherding 第三人称单数: shepherds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lend', '[lend]', 'v.借给；贷款；借(出)', '1. Would you please lend me your pencil? 请把铅笔借给我用用好吗？ 2. I can\'t possibly lend you so much money. 我没有可能借给你这麽多钱。 3. The bank refused to lend the money to us. 银行拒绝向我们贷款。 4. Lend me your typewriter, please. 请把你的打字机借我用一下。', '名词: lender 过去式: lent 过去分词: lent 现在分词: lending 第三人称单数: lends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rear', '[rɪr]', 'adj.后面的；后方的；背面的 n.后部；尾部；后方 v.举起；养育；饲养', '1. You should keep your front and rear lights in good working order. 你应该使你的前后灯保持好的工作状态。 2. A driver can see the road behind him by looking at the rear view mirror. 汽车司机通过反光镜能看到他身后的路。 3. The sun shines through the rear window. 太阳从后窗照射进来。 4. The main entrance is at the rear. 主要入口在后面。 5. The snake reared its head. 那蛇扬起了头。', '名词: rearer 过去式: reared 过去分词: reared 现在分词: rearing 第三人称单数: rears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overall', '[ˌoʊvər\'ɔːl]', 'adj.全部的；总体的；全面考虑的 adv.总的来说；总共 n.罩衫；工作服', '1. The overall measurement of this room is 80 square meters. 这个屋子的总面积是80平方米。 2. Please provide your overall evaluation. 请给出你的总体评价。 3. There\'s been an overall improvement recently. 近来各方面都有所改进。 4. Overall, the tone of the book is satirical. 总的说来,这本书是讽刺性的。 5. The shop assistant was wearing a white overall. 那店员穿著白色长罩衣。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('legal', '[\'liːɡl]', 'adj.法定的；法律的；合法的', '1. When his father died, his uncle became his legal custodian. 他父亲死后,他叔叔成了他的法定监护人。 2. She started out on her legal career in 1963. 她于1963年干起了法律这一行。 3. We will introduce legal safeguards against fraud. 我们要采取法律保护措施，制止诈骗活动。 4. When you are 18, you are a legal voter. 当你满18岁的时候，你就是一个合法的投票者。', '副词: legally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('apt', '[æpt]', 'adj.恰当的；聪明的；易于 ... 的 abbr.公寓（=apartment） abbr.才能；天资（=aptitude）', '1. In many ways, the comparison is apt. 在诸多方面，这个对比是恰当的。 2. I imagine that you may deduce an apt moral from my tale. 我觉得你也许能从我的际遇中引出恰当的教训。 3. Henry is an apt student of the practical science. 亨利在实践科学上是个聪明的学生。 4. He is a clever boy but apt to get into mischief. 他是个聪明却很调皮的孩子。 5. He has a handful of intelligent and apt students. 他有许多天资聪颖的学生。', '副词: aptly 名词: aptness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rigorous', '[\'rɪɡərəs]', 'adj.严格的；严厉的；严峻的；细致的', '1. The planes have to undergo rigorous safety checks. 这些飞机得接受非常严格的安全检查。 2. The work failed to meet their rigorous standards. 工作没有达到他们的严格标准。 3. It further implements the safe production responsibility system, and enforces rigorous safe production laws and regulations and a related accountability system. 进一步实行安全生产责任体系，加强严厉的安全生产法规和相关责任体系。 4. He lived through the rigorous trials of revolutionary war. 他经受了革命战争的严峻考验。', '副词: rigorously 名词: rigorousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('movement', '[\'muːvmənt]', 'n.活动；运动；动作；[音]乐章', '1. If you did so, you would lose the movement of the knee. 如果你这样做,你的膝关节就不能活动了。 2. Loose clothing gives you greater freedom of movement. 衣服宽松，可以活动自如。 3. The Trade Union Movement works to obtain higher wages and better conditions. 工会运动旨在争取更高的工资和更好的工作条件。 4. The leadership of the movement are in agreement on this issue. 这一运动的领导层对这个问题的看法一致。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('renew', '[rɪ\'nuː]', 'v.重新开始；更新', '1. The trees renew their foliage every year. 树木每年都重新长出叶子。 2. I must renew the water in the fish-tank. 我一定要给鱼箱重新注满水。 3. It is impossible to renew one\'s youth. 重新恢复青春是不可能的。 4. I shall renew my request for a vote. 我将重新要求投票表决。', '名词: renewer 过去式: renewed 过去分词: renewed 现在分词: renewing 第三人称单数: renews');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('domain', '[doʊ\'meɪn]', 'n.领地；领域；范围', '1. Each of her cousins had charge of his own domain. 她的每一个亲属主管着自己的领地。 2. The kitchen is my wife\'s domain, and she doesn\'t like me going into it. 厨房是我妻子的领地,她不愿让我进去。 3. As soon as you create an account for the user, the user can participate in a secure domain. 一旦您为用户创建了一个帐号，用户就可以进入安全域中。 4. The doctor works in the domain of public health. 医生在公众健康范围内工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fancy', '[\'fænsi]', 'adj.华丽装饰的；复杂的；引人注目的；时髦的；昂贵的；好的 n.喜爱；幻想；想像力 vt.想象；希望；迷恋', '1. She wants to buy a handbag, not fancy but strong. 我想买一个手提包不要花俏,而要耐用。 2. These fancy arguments befuddled us. 这些复杂的论据令我们疑惑不已。 3. All eyes were rested on the fancy car. 所有的眼神都注视那部新奇的车。 4. A fancy hairstyle will be great for a party. 参加晚会梳个时尚发型很不错。 5. The painting took his fancy, so he bought it. 这幅画被他看中了,所以他就把它买了下来。 6. I fancy they\'re getting on well with each other. 我猜想他们相处得不错。', '副词: fancily 比较级: fancier 最高级: fanciest 名词: fanciness 名词复数: fancies 过去式: fancied 过去分词: fancied 现在分词: fancying 第三人称单数: fancies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impossible', '[ɪm\'pɑːsəbl]', 'adj.不可能的；做不到的', '1. It\'s impossible to tell who will win the next election. 下届选举谁能获胜无法预知。 2. It\'s impossible for us to finish the work in one day. 我们在一天之内完成这份工作是不可能的。', '副词: impossibly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('existence', '[ɪɡ\'zɪstəns]', 'n.存在；生存', '1. The newspaper ceased to appear after an existence of three months. 该报发行3 个月后停刊了。 2. According to some philosopher, everything in existence is reasonable. 某位哲学家认为，存在的事物都是合理的。 3. The family lived a precarious existence. 这家人过着朝不保夕的生活。 4. Pollution poses a threat to the continued existence of this species. 污染对这一物种的继续生存造成了威胁。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('participant', '[pɑːr\'tɪsɪpənt]', 'n.参与者', '1. She is an active participant in this activity. 她积极参与这项活动。 2. He is an active participant in the civil rights movement. 他是人权运动的积极参加者。 3. Each participant is to pay his own expenses. 每个参与者都必须自费。', '名词: participance');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('naked', '[\'neɪkɪd]', 'adj.裸体的；无掩饰的；明白的；无覆盖的', '1. These little boys swim naked in the river. 这些小孩光着身子在河里游泳。 2. The men of this tribe used to go naked. 这个部落里的男子过去常是裸体的。 3. Craft must have clothes,but truth love to go naked. 欺诈必须伪装，真理不须掩饰。 4. This in itself is naked deprivation [of rights]. 这本身就是赤裸裸的剥夺。', '副词: nakedly 名词: nakedness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('treasure', '[\'treʒər]', 'n.财富；宝物 vt.珍藏；珍视', '1. A nation\'s treasure is in its scholars. 学者是国家的财富。 2. This museum has many art treasures. 这家博物馆收藏了许多艺术珍品。 3. They went to the cave in quest of hidden treasure. 他们到山洞去寻找宝藏。 4. I shall always treasure the memory of our meetings. 我将永远记住我们相聚的情景。', '形容词: treasurable 过去式: treasured 过去分词: treasured 现在分词: treasuring 第三人称单数: treasures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nice', '[naɪs]', 'adj.好的；美妙的；友好的；令人愉快的；精细的', '1. It\'s a nice day today. 今天天气很好。 2. How nice of you to do that! 你那样做真是太好了！ 3. I brought her a very nice present from Soochow. 我从苏州给她带来一件美妙的礼物。 4. People there are very nice to tourists and foreigners. 那儿的人们对待旅行者和外国人都非常友好。', '副词: nicely 比较级: nicer 最高级: nicest 名词: niceness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('opt', '[ɑːpt]', 'vi.选择；决定', '1. They opt for more holiday instead of more pay. 他们选择了延长假期而不是增加工资。 2. It\'s difficult to opt from so many choices. 从那样多可供选择的东西中做选择是困难的。 3. Employees may opt out of the company\'s pension plan. 雇员可选择不参加该公司的养老金计划。 4. He opted to go to Paris rather than London. 他决定去巴黎，不去伦敦。', '过去式: opted 过去分词: opted 现在分词: opting 第三人称单数: opts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('artist', '[\'ɑːrtɪst]', 'n.艺术家；美术家；艺人', '1. She is a consummate artist. 她是个技艺高超的艺术家。 2. He is a notable artist. 他是一位著名的艺术家。 3. His dream of becoming an artist has been fulfilled. 他成为一个艺术家的梦想实现了。 4. The vital spark in him makes him an artist. 他生气勃勃的活力使他成为一个艺术家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compete', '[kəm\'piːt]', 'v.竞争；比赛；对抗', '1. Companies must be able to compete in the marketplace. 公司一定要在市场中有竞争力。 2. Several companies are competing for the contract. 几家公司正为争取一项合同而互相竞争。 3. We can compete with the best teams. 我们能与最好的队竞争。 4. He\'s hoping to compete in the London marathon. 他期盼着参加伦敦马拉松比赛。', '过去式: competed 过去分词: competed 现在分词: competing 第三人称单数: competes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('same', '[seɪm]', 'adj.同样的，一样的 adv.同样地 pron.同样的人或事', '1. He praised my work and in the same breath told me I would have to leave. 他称赞我工作好，刚说完这话就让我离职。 2. I resigned on Friday and left that same day. 我星期五辞职後当天就离开了。 3. Father sits in the same chair every evening. 父亲每晚都坐在同一张椅子上， 4. I think the same of him as you do. 我对他的看法和你一样。 5. Their ages are the same. 他们的年龄相同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spot', '[spɑːt]', 'n.地点；场所；职位；污点；斑点；少量；聚光灯；插播节目 adj.现场的；现货的；插播的 v.（使）产生污渍；玷污；认出；用灯光照射', '1. This is the spot where the two trucks collided. 这儿就是两辆卡车相撞的地点。 2. That was the common spot for settling affairs of honour. 那是他们通常决斗的场所。 3. She found a spot as a secretary. 她找到一个秘书的职位。 4. He flicked at spot with handkerchief. 他轻轻地用手帕拂拭污点。 5. Several television stations gave spot coverage to the conference. 好几家电视台对大会作了现场报导。 6. His boots were spotted with mud. 他的靴子上沾有泥渍。', '形容词: spottable 过去式: spotted 过去分词: spotted 现在分词: spotting 第三人称单数: spots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('female', '[\'fiːmeɪl]', 'adj.女性的；雌性的 n.女性；雌性动物；[植]雌株', '1. The male and female genders are equal. 男性和女性是平等的。 2. All the female workers in this factory got a present on March 8th. 这家工厂的所有女职工在三八节都得到了一份礼物。 3. The male sperm fertilizes the female egg. 雄性的精子使雌性的卵子受精。 4. The male is physically stronger than the female. 男性在身体上要比女性强壮。', '名词: femaleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('goat', '[ɡoʊt]', 'n.山羊；色鬼；替罪羊', '1. Can you distinguish goat from sheep? 你能把山羊和绵羊区分开吗？ 2. We saw the tiger pouncing on the goat. 我们看见老虎向那只山羊扑过去。 3. The regimental mascot is a goat. 这个团的吉祥物是山羊。 4. The high priest sacrificed the goat on the altar. 大祭司把山羊供奉在祭坛上。', '形容词: goatish');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('male', '[meɪl]', 'adj.男性的；雄性的 n.男子；雄性动物', '1. The male voice is deeper than the female. 男性的嗓音比女性的低沉。 2. We need some male subjects for a psychology experiment. 我们需要几个男子作心理学实验对象。 3. In early days only male athletes were allowed to take part in the Olympic Games. 在奥林匹克运动会早期，只有男性运动员才能参加比赛。 4. This flower is a male flower. 这朵花是雄花。 5. The male is physically stronger than the female. 男性在身体上要比女性强壮。', '名词: maleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('levy', '[\'levi]', 'n.征税；召集 vt.征收；发动 vi.强收', '1. The basis of the proposals is a levy of 0.25 per cent. 建议的征税基点为百分之零点二五。 2. The nation levied all able-bodied man for the war. 国家征召所有壮丁参战。 3. The government has decided to levy a tax on import cars. 政府决定征收进口汽车税。 4. The nation levied all able-bodied man for the war. 国家征召所有壮丁参战。 5. The court may have to levy on your estate to pay your debts. 法庭可能不得不扣押你的房地产，用来偿付你的债务。', '名词: levier 名词复数: levies 过去式: levied 过去分词: levied 现在分词: levying 第三人称单数: levies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mob', '[mɑːb]', 'n.暴民；一伙；[贬]民众 vt.大举包围；蜂拥而入', '1. The mob rampaged through the village. 这伙暴徒在村中横冲直撞。 2. The speaker was roughly handled by the mob. 演说者受到暴民的粗暴对待。 3. A mob of youths had been dogging me for some time. 一段时间以来一伙年轻人一直在尾随着我。 4. More sinister is the involvement of the heavy mob. 更危险的是众多无知民众的卷入。 5. Pop stars are always moaning about being mobbed by their fans. 流行歌星总是抱怨他们受到歌迷的包围。', '形容词: mobbish 副词: mobbishly 过去式: mobbed 过去分词: mobbed 现在分词: mobbing 第三人称单数: mobs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assembly', '[ə\'sembli]', 'n.集会；集合；议会；装配；与会者；聚集在一起的人；[计]汇编', '1. The assembly of students takes place in the auditorium. 学生们在大礼堂举行集会。 2. He rang the bell for school assembly. 他敲钟通知全校集合。 3. Each state had a governor and a state assembly. 每一州都有一个州长和州议会。 4. Jack was assigned to the assembly shop of the factory. 杰克被分配到厂里的装配间工作。', '名词复数: assemblies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('noon', '[nuːn]', 'n.正午；中午；全盛期；顶点', '1. At noon, the sun is high in the sky. 正午，烈日当空。 2. We need to be there before noon. 我们要在正午前赶到那儿。 3. She anchors a 45-minute news show at noon. 她每天中午主持四十五分钟的新闻广播。 4. We were through with the work towards noon. 将近中午时我们把工作做完了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accord', '[ə\'kɔːrd]', 'n.协议；一致；符合 v.与...一致；给予；调解', '1. The two countries reached an accord. 两国签订了一项协议。 2. His words are in accord with his ideas. 他心口一致。 3. Their views were found to be in perfect accord. 人们发现他们的意见是完全一致的。 4. Your behavior is not in accord with your principle. 你的行为与你的原则不符。 5. Our information does not accord with his reports. 我们所了解的情况与他的报告不一致。', '过去式: accorded 过去分词: accorded 现在分词: according 第三人称单数: accords');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nuisance', '[\'nuːsns]', 'n.讨厌的人；讨厌的东西；伤害', '1. He was a boring nuisance! I\'m glad to be rid of him. 他这人真讨厌! 我很庆幸能摆脱他的纠缠。 2. Don\'t make yourself a nuisance to others. 不要做一个令人讨厌的人。 3. This work is a cursed nuisance. 这种工作讨厌死了。 4. What a nuisance! 真讨厌！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('June', '[dʒuːn]', 'n.六月 n.琼(女子名)', '1. This weather is exceptional for June. 六月里这样的天气是反常的。 2. He started work here last June. 他是去年六月开始在这里工作的。 3. She came in June, when it was very hot. 她六月来，那时天气非常热。 4. This tender should be submitted by June 26th. 此投标书应于六月二十六日前提交。 5. If there\'s any news June will soon sniff it out. 只要有新闻，琼总是会马上知道的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hypocrisy', '[hɪ\'pɑːkrəsi]', 'n.伪善', '1. We were cheated by his hypocrisy. 我们都被他的伪善欺骗了。 2. I have no brow of such worldly hypocrisy. 我讨厌这种老于世故的伪善。', '名词复数: hypocrisies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ash', '[æʃ]', 'n.灰；灰烬 n.白蜡树；白蜡木 (复)ashes：骨灰；废墟；苍白.', '1. She dusted some ash from her sleeve. 她撢去袖子上的灰末。 2. Wood ash should be forked or dug into the soil. 木灰应被耙入或插进土壤里。 3. I wish he would refrain from scattering his ash all over the carpet. 我希望他不要将烟灰往地毯上乱弹。 4. The fire reduced the house to a mass of ash. 大火把房子烧成了灰烬。 5. There was an ash tree in the forest which was thought to be a monster. 森林中有一株被认为是妖怪的白蜡树。 6. Marilyn\'s pitted skin, breasts of carved pumice, volcanic thighs, a face of ash. 玛丽莲凹凸不平的皮肤，浮石雕刻般的双乳，火山似的大腿，死一样苍白的脸。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('actress', '[\'æktrəs]', 'n.女演员', '1. The actress received numerous floral tributes. 那位女演员接受了许多献花。 2. Her success as an actress was now assured. 她当演员很成功，已毋庸置疑了。 3. She has romantic notions about becoming a famous actress. 她心里充满幻想，总希望有一天会成为著名演员。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('site', '[saɪt]', 'n.地点；位置；现场 vt.使 ... 位于', '1. That sale precludes further development on this site. 卖出以后妨碍了这一地点的进一步发展。 2. The site is being developed by a London property company. 这块地正在由伦敦的一家地产公司开发利用。 3. Excavation of the site will begin tomorrow. 明天开始挖掘工作。 4. The house is built on the site of a medieval prison. 这个房屋建立在中世纪监狱的位置。 5. Is it safe to site the power station here? 在这建造发电厂安全吗？', '过去式: sited 过去分词: sited 现在分词: siting 第三人称单数: sites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('score', '[skɔː]', 'vt.得分；获胜；刻划；划线；批评；给 ... 谱曲 n.得分；刻痕；二十；乐谱 vi.得分；记分；得胜', '1. Hughes scored two goals before half-time. 休斯在上半场进了两个球. 2. The army continued to score successes in the south. 军队在南方不断取得胜利。 3. They scored the floor-boards by pushing furniture about. 他们推动家具 4. could you please score my name off? 请把我的名字从名单中划掉好吗? 5. I recorded the score in a notebook. 我在笔记本上记下了分数。 6. The home team has yet to score. 主队还没有得分.', '名词: scorer 过去式: scored 过去分词: scored 现在分词: scoring 第三人称单数: scores');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fellow', '[\'feloʊ]', 'n.家伙；同事；同伴；研究员；校董 adj.同伴的；同事的；同类的', '1. Jack is a clever fellow indeed. 杰克确实是个聪明的家伙。 2. I can\'t tolerate that rude fellow. 我不能容忍那个粗鲁的家伙。 3. That foolish fellow is looking for trouble. 那个愚蠢的家伙在自找麻烦。 4. He\'s a very nice fellow though bad-tempered. 他虽然脾气暴躁,但是一个很好的同事。 5. He recalled his fellow traveller with pleasure. 他愉快地回忆起他的旅伴。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guilty', '[\'ɡɪlti]', 'adj.有罪的；内疚的', '1. The court found him guilty. 法官判他有罪。 2. The man was proved guilty of murder. 这个男子被证实犯了杀人罪。 3. A man is accounted innocent until he is proven guilty. 一个人未被证明有罪前，被视为是清白的。 4. His answer evidenced a guilty conscience. 他的回答证明他良心有愧。', '副词: guiltily 比较级: guiltier 最高级: guiltiest 名词: guiltiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('material', '[mə\'tɪriəl]', 'n.材料；原料；素材；资料；题材；物质 adj.物质的；重要的；关键的；肉体上的；实质性的', '1. The colour in this silk material will not fade. 这种绸布料子不会褪色。 2. The workshop has shut down for lack of raw material. 由于缺乏原料，这个车间已停工了。 3. She\'s collecting materials for her latest novel. 她在为其最新的小说收集素材。 4. He was grubbing about in the public library for materials. 他正在公共图书馆里寻找资料。 5. Material wealth doesn\'t equal spiritual wealth. 物质的财富并不代表精神的财富!', '名词: materialness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shirt', '[ʃɜːrt]', 'n.衬衫 v.给…穿上衬衫', '1. She shortened the shirt by an inch. 她把衬衫截短了一英寸。 2. What size of collar is this shirt? 这衬衣领子的尺寸是多少？ 3. Will you stitch a button on this shirt? 请你在这件衬衫上钉一颗钮扣好吗？ 4. Would you sew this button onto my shirt? 请你把这颗纽扣缝到我的衬衫上好吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mankind', '[mæn\'kaɪnd]', 'n.人类；男人', '1. Mankind learns its first language in early childhood. 人类是在幼年开始学习第一种语言的。 2. Christ\'s atonement is for the sins of mankind. 耶稣的赎罪是为了人类的罪恶。 3. Sympathy is the feeling characteristic of mankind. 同情心是人类特有的感情。 4. Genetic engineering will have revolutionary consequences for mankind. 遗传工程将对人类产生深远的影响。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('warmth', '[wɔːrmθ]', 'n.温暖；热烈；热情；热心', '1. The sun gives (us) warmth and light. 太阳供给我们光和热。 2. She sheds warmth and happiness around her. 她给周围的人带来温暖兴幸福。 3. He was pleased by the warmth of his welcome. 他因受到热烈欢迎而高兴。 4. He was touched by the warmth of their welcome. 他受到他们热情欢迎，十分感动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('downtown', '[ˌdaʊn\'taʊn]', 'n.市中心区；市中心 adj.市中心的', '1. Most of the old buildings in the downtown were plucked down, and new ones erected. 市中心的大部分建筑物都拆掉了，建起了新的房子。 2. A new skyscraper has been put up downtown. 市中心又建起了一座摩天大厦。 3. The family lived far away from downtown. 那家人住在离市中心很远的地方。 4. Most of the old buildings in the downtown were plucked down, and new ones erected. 市中心的大部分建筑物都拆掉了，建起了新的房子。 5. I have an apartment in downtown Manhattan. 我在曼哈顿中心区有一套住房。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('famine', '[\'fæmɪn]', 'n.饥荒；极度缺乏', '1. War, famine and flood are terrible evils. 战争、饥荒和洪水都是可怕的灾祸。 2. Famine is often the sequel to war or drought. 饥荒往往是战争或干旱造成的。 3. It\'s impossible to remain unmoved by her reports of the famine. 任何人对她报道的饥荒情况都不可能无动于衷。 4. We are collecting money for the famine victim. 我们在为遭受饥荒的灾民募捐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plea', '[pliː]', 'n.恳求；申诉；抗辩；借口', '1. The prisoner made a plea for mercy. 囚犯恳求宽恕。 2. She made an impassioned plea for justice. 她激昂地抗辩，恳求获得公正。 3. In making that plea he will breathe in vain. 他做那种恳求是白费口舌的。 4. The thief entered a plea of not guilty. 这个贼提出了无罪申诉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('boat', '[boʊt]', 'n.船；船型物 v.划船；放于船上；乘船', '1. They pushed the boat further into the water. 他们把小船又往水里推了推。 2. Let\'s go boating on the lake. 我们去湖上划船吧。 3. Are you going to America by boat or by plane? 你到美国是坐船还是坐飞机？ 4. Don\'t miss the boat. 不要坐失良机。 5. They are training for the boat race. 他们正在为划船比赛接受训练。', '过去式: boated 过去分词: boated 现在分词: boating 第三人称单数: boats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('competitive', '[kəm\'petətɪv]', 'adj.竞争的；有竞争力的；胜过或超过他人的', '1. It\'s getting very competitive in the car industry. 汽车工业方面的竞争日益加剧。 2. Nobody can entirely keep away from this competitive world. 没有人能够完全远离这个竞争社会。 3. Ford has a more competitive environment. 福特公司具有一个较有竞争力的环境。 4. Our prices are competitive. 我们的价格是有竞争性的。', '副词: competitively 名词: competitiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('close', '[kloʊs]', 'v.关；合拢；不开放；停业；结束；收盘；（使）缩小；牢牢握住或抓住；（使）靠拢；同意；短兵相接 adj.亲近的；近的；几乎的；闷热的；严密的；紧凑的；剪得很短的；守口如瓶的；吝啬的；势均力敌的 adv.接近；靠近；紧紧地 n.死胡同；完结；结论', '1. If you close your eyes, you can\'t see anything. 如果你闭上眼睛，就什么也看不见了。 2. The road was closed to traffic for two days. 这条路已经封路两天了。 3. The hospital closed at the end of last year. 这所医院去年年底关闭。 4. He closed his speech with a funny joke. 他用一则有趣的笑话结束了演讲。 5. I believe you and he were very close friends. 我相信你和他是亲密无间的朋友。 6. They live quite close. 他们住得很近. 7. He soon brought the meeting to a close. 他很快就结束了会见。', '副词: closely 比较级: closer 最高级: closest 名词: closeness 过去式: closed 过去分词: closed 现在分词: closing 第三人称单数: closes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aspect', '[\'æspekt]', 'n.方面；方位；外观；外貌', '1. This is only one aspect of the problem. 这只是问题的一个方面。 2. He has made progress in every aspect. 他在各方面都有起色。 3. The building has a southern aspect. 那座建筑是朝南的。 4. The open spaces differ according to aspect. 开敞空地随方位而不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('admit', '[əd\'mɪt]', 'vt.承认；允许进入；给…进入的权利；容纳 vi.承认；允许进入；允许', '1. He made a terrible mistake, but he refused to admit it. 他犯了一个严重的错误,可是他拒不承认。 2. We have to admit that there is still room for improvement. 我们不得不承认,在这方面有尚待改进的地方。 3. Each ticket admits two people to the party. 每张票可供两人入场参加聚会。 4. I reluctantly admitted to being nervous about the test. 我勉强承认我对测试感到紧张。', '过去式: admitted 过去分词: admitted 现在分词: admitting 第三人称单数: admits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('birth', '[bɜːrθ]', 'n.分娩；出生；诞生；血统 v.分娩；产生 adj.有血亲关系的', '1. Gestation extends from fertilization to birth. 妊娠期系指从配种到分娩之间的时间。 2. Many of the women died in child birth in the past. 在过去，许多妇女死于分娩。 3. My daughter\'s birth was ecstatic. 我女儿的出生令人欣喜。 4. By accident of birth she was rich. 她有幸出生于富裕人家。 5. Gestation extends from fertilization to birth. 妊娠期系指从配种到分娩之间的时间。', '过去式: birthed 过去分词: birthed 现在分词: birthing 第三人称单数: births');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drown', '[draʊn]', 'vi.淹死 vt.淹死；淹没', '1. The little girl drowned in the river. 小女孩在河里淹死了。 2. If you can keep your head above water, you won\'t drown. 如果能让头露出水面，你就不会被淹死。 3. It is cruel to drown the cat in the river. 把猫淹死在河里是件残忍的事。 4. The band drowned our conversation. 乐队的演奏声把我们谈话的声音淹没了。', '过去式: drowned 过去分词: drowned 现在分词: drowning 第三人称单数: drowns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adolescent', '[ˌædə\'lesnt]', 'adj.青春期的；青少年的 n.青少年', '1. It is not unusual for grown adults to act in an adolescent way. 成人表现出青春期的样子很正常。 2. She says that risk-taking is normal adolescent behaviour. 她说冒险是青春期的正常表现。 3. I still remember my adolescent life. 我仍然记得我青少年时期的生活。 4. The adolescent period is one\'s best time. 青少年时期是一个人最美好的一段时光。 5. Overgrowth is common in adolescents. 青少年成长过快是普遍现象。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guy', '[ɡaɪ]', 'n.家伙；(男)人 n.拉索；牵索 vt.嘲笑', '1. This ordinary quiet guy just freaked out and shot ten people. 这个平时温和的家伙简直发疯了，开枪打死了十个人。 2. I made a harmless remark to some guy at the bar and he swung at me. 在酒吧里我向某个家伙说了句无恶意的话，他就向我打了一拳。 3. He\'s a nice guy. 他是个好人。 4. Sean is really a very sweet guy and loaded with talent. 西恩真是一个讨人喜欢的小伙，而且多才多艺。 5. Gather all your friends and laugh to tears when the poor guy starts farting. 召集你的朋友一起嘲笑那个被整的放屁朋友。', '过去式: guyed 过去分词: guyed 现在分词: guying 第三人称单数: guys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('button', '[\'bʌtn]', 'n.纽扣；按钮 v.扣上纽扣；用纽扣装饰', '1. One of the buttons has come off my coat. 我上衣上的一颗扣子掉了。 2. You may stop the machine by pushing this button. 按下这个按钮你就可以关掉这个机器。 3. It\'s very warm, he didn\'t even button his coat. 天气很暖和,他甚至都没扣他外衣的钮扣。', '形容词: buttony 名词: buttoner 过去式: buttoned 过去分词: buttoned 现在分词: buttoning 第三人称单数: buttons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('initiative', '[ɪ\'nɪʃətɪv]', 'adj.自发的 n.首创精神；主动权；第一步；倡议；项目', '1. She took an initiative part in the Wildlife Conservation Society. 她主动参加野生动物保护协会。 2. It is innovation plus initiative that has kept it thriving. 创新与进取精神使得它蓬勃发展。 3. In the economic trend of the new era, having the initiative is the key. 在新时期的经济大潮中，拥有主动权是关键。 4. Thus the initiative was lost at the very first move, and that is really the worst and most stupid way to fight. 开脚一步就丧失了主动权，真是最蠢最坏的打法。', '副词: initiatively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('license', '[\'laɪsns]', 'n.许可证；执照；特许 vt.发许可证给；特许', '1. We contemplate obtaining a technical license. 我们希望获得一项技术许可证。 2. His license was suspended for six months. 他的执照被吊销6个月。 3. The designers were allowed a lot of creative license. 那些设计者们获得了很多创意许可。 4. Are you licensed to drive? 你得到驾车的执照了吗？', '形容词: licensable 名词: licenser 过去式: licensed 过去分词: licensed 现在分词: licensing 第三人称单数: licenses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('little', '[\'lɪtl]', 'adj.小的；幼小的；短的；微不足道的；少到几乎没有的 adv.甚少；毫不；难得 n.极少', '1. We have a little bull session after work. 下班后，我们要开一个小的讨论会。 2. This little bed will do for our youngest daughter. 这张小床我们最小的女儿睡能行。 3. She is too little to ride a bicycle. 她太小了，不能骑脚踏车。 4. She walked away and her little heart was broken. 她走开了但是她幼小的心却受伤了。 5. He is little known as an artist. 他是个不出名的艺术家。 6. The little that I have seen of his work is satisfactory. 他的工作就我所见的那一小部分而言是令人满意的。', '比较级: littler/less/lesser 最高级: littlest/least 名词: littleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stove', '[stoʊv]', 'n.炉子；窑；【主英】温室', '1. I have to buy a more economical stove. 我得买一个更节省燃料的火炉。 2. Please warm up this milk over the stove. 请把这杯牛奶放在炉子上热一热。 3. The erected stove is specially made for firing limestone. 这座立窑是专门用来烧制石灰石的。 4. These stove plants are looked after by gardeners. 园艺员照料着温室的植物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tumble', '[\'tʌmbl]', 'v.暴跌；倒塌；跌倒；翻滚；弄乱；明白；突然发现 n.暴跌；跌跤；混乱', '1. Share prices tumbled on the stock-market. 股市上股票价格暴跌。 2. Stock market price tumble after rumor of a rise in interest rate. 谣传利率上升之後，股票市场价格猛跌。 3. That old building could tumble down at any time. 那座古老的楼房随时可能倒塌。 4. It only needed a push and the whole building will come tumble down. 只要稍稍一推，那整幢房子就会倒塌下来。 5. Stock prices took a tumble in the afternoon. 股票价格下午猛跌。', '过去式: tumbled 过去分词: tumbled 现在分词: tumbling 第三人称单数: tumbles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sensitive', '[\'sensətɪv]', 'adj.灵敏的；敏感的；感光的；易受伤害的；善解人意的 n.敏感的人', '1. She\'s got very sensitive hearing, skin, etc. 她的听觉、 触觉等很灵敏。 2. Don\'t be so sensitive and I was not criticizing you. 别那么敏感,我不是在批评你。 3. What food and fruit are sensitive? 哪些食物和水果是感光的？ 4. The film is coated with light sensitive chemicals, which are change by the different shades and colors of light. 胶卷上涂了一层感光的化学物质，这些物质因光的不同色度与颜色而改变。', '副词: sensitively 名词: sensitiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tile', '[taɪl]', 'n.瓷砖；瓦片 v.盖瓦；铺瓷砖', '1. The reconciled reptiles rest on a fragile tile. 和解的爬行动物歇在易碎的瓷砖上。 2. We have put tiles on the wall behind the bath. 我们在浴缸后的墙上贴了瓷砖。 3. I entered the kitchen, with its old tile floor and its cherrywood cabinets. 我走进了厨房，年月久远的瓷砖地面，樱桃木材质的各色橱柜。 4. The rain came in for want of tile on the roof. 因房顶缺少瓦片，雨渗进来了。', '过去式: tiled 过去分词: tiled 现在分词: tiling 第三人称单数: tiles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('culture', '[\'kʌltʃər]', 'n.栽培；文化；教养 vt.培养，栽培', '1. He has to learn the culture of bees. 他得学养蜂。 2. She has studied the cultures of Oriental countries. 她研究过东方各国的文化。 3. He is a man of little culture. 他没多少文化修养。 4. The culture of the mind is vital. 修心养性是极其重要的。', '过去式: cultured 过去分词: cultured 现在分词: culturing 第三人称单数: cultures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('taste', '[teɪst]', 'n.味觉；味道；尝试；品味；爱好 v.品尝；有 ... 味道的；体验', '1. I\'ve got a cold and so I have lost my sense of taste. 我伤风了,尝不出味道。 2. The medicine has a bitter taste. 这药有苦味。 3. She likes her first taste of life in a big city. 她喜欢她对大城市生活的初次体验。 4. She has good taste in clothes. 她对服装有很好的审美眼光。 5. That\'s the best wine I\'ve ever tasted. 那是我喝过的最好的酒', '形容词: tastable 过去式: tasted 过去分词: tasted 现在分词: tasting 第三人称单数: tastes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bomb', '[bɑːm]', 'n.炸弹 vt.轰炸；投弹于 vi.投弹；失败', '1. The bomb exploded in a twinkling. 炸弹一会儿就爆炸了。 2. The terrorists planted a bomb in the post office. 恐怖分子在邮局安放了一枚炸弹。 3. The city was bombed by the enemy. 这座城市被敌人炸毁了。 4. Our parents were bombed out twice during the war. 我们的父母在战争期间有两次被炸弹炸得无家可归。 5. The enemies bombed in a remote village. 敌人在一个偏僻的村庄投下了炸弹。', '过去式: bombed 过去分词: bombed 现在分词: bombing 第三人称单数: bombs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reason', '[\'riːzn]', 'n.原因；理由；理智；理性 v.理论；论证；推理；劝说', '1. That is the reason why I don\'t like it. 那就是我不喜欢它的原因。 2. He is able to explain the reason because he was present at that time. 他当时在场,所以他能解释原因。 3. We have reason to believe that he was murdered. 我们有理由相信他是被谋杀的。 4. We shall in no way let reason be defeated by impulse. 我们决不能让冲动战胜理智。 5. Who can reason with you when you are so stubborn? 你这么执拗的时候,谁能和你理论?', '名词: reasoner 过去式: reasoned 过去分词: reasoned 现在分词: reasoning 第三人称单数: reasons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('requirement', '[rɪ\'kwaɪərmənt]', 'n.必要条件；要求', '1. Candidates who fail to meet these requirements will not be admitted to the University. 不符合这些要求的考生不能上这所大学。 2. Our immediate requirement is extra staff. 我们亟需增加工作人员。 3. The refugees\' main requirements are food and shelter. 难民的主要必需品是食物和住所。', '动词: require 名词复数: requirements');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tie', '[taɪ]', 'n.束缚；使人结合在一起的事物；领带；绳；不分胜负 v.系；约束；捆绑；打结；连结', '1. He doesn\'t want any ties; that\'s why he never married. 他不愿受束缚，所以不结婚。 2. Pets can be a tie when you want to go away on holiday. 要想外出度假时，宠物会成为牵累。 3. The firm has ties with an American corporation. 该商行与美国一家公司有关系。 4. They want to loosen their ties with Britain. 他们想要削弱同英国的关系。 5. I was all thumbs this morning. I couldn\'t even tie my shoelaces. 今天早上我笨手笨脚的,连鞋带都系不好了。', '过去式: tied 过去分词: tied 现在分词: tying 第三人称单数: ties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stop', '[stɑːp]', 'v.停止；阻止；停留 n.停止；逗留；车站', '1. The train stopped at the station. 火车在车站上停了下来。 2. His heart has stopped. 他的心脏停止了跳动。 3. They would stop the rich from robbing the poor. 他们要制止富人掠夺穷人。 4. I only just managed to stop myself from shouting at him. 我极力控制住自己没对他喊叫起来。 5. They put a stop to the evils. 他们杜绝了这些坏事。', '形容词: stoppable 过去式: stopped 过去分词: stopped 现在分词: stopping 第三人称单数: stops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('potato', '[pə\'teɪtoʊ]', 'n.马铃薯；土豆', '1. The potato is a vegetable, not a fruit. 马铃薯是一种蔬菜，不是一种水果。 2. This salad is made of apple, pear, potato and celery. 这份色拉是由苹果、梨、土豆和芹菜做成的。 3. I like to cook dishes with potatoes. 我喜欢用马铃薯炒菜。 4. Would you like more mashed potato? 在来点马铃薯泥好吗？', '名词复数: potatoes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trash', '[træʃ]', 'n.废物；垃圾 vt.废弃；捣毁；擦去 vi.捣毁', '1. The doctors eliminated trash from his body. 医生们帮他排除体内废物。 2. I no longer consider people on welfare white trash. 我不再认为靠福利救济的人是白人当中的废物。 3. Please take the trash to the garbage can. 请将垃圾拿到垃圾筒去。 4. People shouldn\'t dump trash on public land. 人们不应在公共场所倾倒垃圾。 5. Trash that old thing and buy a new one. 扔掉老的再买一个新的吧。 6. The marching turned to trashing. 游行队伍开始动手捣毁东西了。', '过去式: trashed 过去分词: trashed 现在分词: trashing 第三人称单数: trashes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hospitality', '[ˌhɑːspɪ\'tæləti]', 'n.款待；殷勤；好客；酒店管理', '1. I received the hospitality of the family. 我受到这家人亲切的款待。 2. I\'d like to thank you for your hospitality. 非常感谢你们的热情款待。 3. The natives are noted for their hospitality. 当地人以殷勤好客闻名。 4. The islanders are known for their hospitality. 岛上的居民以好客闻名。', '名词复数: hospitalities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('confront', '[kən\'frʌnt]', 'vt.对抗；遭遇；面临', '1. We must confront future with optimism. 我们必须乐观地面对未来。 2. You must confront your problems. 你必须面对自己的问题。 3. It\'s no use to confront your boss. 对抗你的老板是没有用的。 4. A soldier often has to confront danger. 士兵常常要身临险境。', '名词: confronter 过去式: confronted 过去分词: confronted 现在分词: confronting 第三人称单数: confronts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rap', '[ræp]', 'n.轻敲；拍击；责骂；厉声说出；说唱音乐；谈话；最少量 vi.轻敲；表演说唱音乐；畅谈', '1. There is a light rap at the door. 有轻轻的敲门声。 2. He took a bad rap on the head when he fell. 他跌倒时头被猛撞了一下。 3. Louise got a bum rap for taking sides with Richard. 路易斯因为偏袒理查德而受到责骂。 4. The bank clerk got a rap on the knuckles for his carelessness. 那个银行职员因为粗心大意而受到责骂。 5. The chairman rapped on the table for order. 主席敲击桌子以维持秩序。', '过去式: rapped 过去分词: rapped 现在分词: rapping 第三人称单数: raps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appreciate', '[ə\'priːʃieɪt]', 'vt.欣赏；赏识；感激；领会；意识到 vi.增值', '1. I really appreciate his complete absorption in his work. 我很欣赏他对工作的极端专注。 2. I\'ve decided to learn photography in order that I may better appreciate the beauty of nature. 我决定学摄影以便能更好地欣赏自然的美。 3. Very few people really appreciate his works. 没人赏识他的作品。 4. His talents are not fully appreciated in that company. 他的才干在那家公司未受到充分赏识。 5. Land will continue to appreciate. 土地将继续增值。', '形容词: appreciatory 名词: appreciator 过去式: appreciated 过去分词: appreciated 现在分词: appreciating 第三人称单数: appreciates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comfortable', '[\'kʌmftəbl]', 'adj.舒适的；充裕的', '1. Were it not for science, we could not live a comfortable live. 若非科学，我们无法过着舒适的生活。 2. Neither chair is comfortable. 两把椅子坐起来都不舒服。 3. A comfortable house may be an Eden. 一个舒适的家可以是一个乐园。 4. She has pretty dancing slippers and comfortable bedroom slippers. 她有漂亮的舞鞋和舒适的卧室拖鞋。', '副词: comfortably 名词: comfortableness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clumsy', '[\'klʌmzi]', 'adj.笨拙的；不得体的；笨重的', '1. The clumsy boy bumped into the table. 笨拙的男孩撞到桌子上。 2. My clumsy answer hurt her feelings. 我笨拙的回答伤了她的感情。 3. He chided his son for being clumsy. 他斥责儿子笨手笨脚。 4. This cobbler is rather clumsy. 这个补鞋匠真是笨手笨脚。', '副词: clumsily 比较级: clumsier 最高级: clumsiest 名词: clumsiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invade', '[ɪn\'veɪd]', 'v.侵略；拥入；侵害；侵扰', '1. When did the Romans invade Britain? 古罗马人是何时侵略英国的? 2. The town was invaded by reporters. 这个城市涌进了大批记者。 3. In the summer tourists invade the mountain village. 夏天游客成群结队地到这个山村来。 4. Germs may invade the organism. 细菌会侵入有机体。', '名词: invader 过去式: invaded 过去分词: invaded 现在分词: invading 第三人称单数: invades');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sign', '[saɪn]', 'n.手势；招牌；符号；迹象；正负号 v.签；签名；做手势；做标记', '1. I talked with him by signs. 我和他用手势交谈。 2. The sign was no longer legible because much of the lettering had worn away. 这块招牌已看不清楚，因为大部分字已磨掉了。 3. Make sure that the sign\'s the right way up. 一定要把符号的上下弄对。 4. There are signs of political unrest in the country. 这个国家有政治不安定的迹象。 5. He signed his name on the cheque. 他在支票上签了名。', '名词: signer 过去式: signed 过去分词: signed 现在分词: signing 第三人称单数: signs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exert', '[ɪɡ\'zɜːrt]', 'vt.运用；施加', '1. He exerted all his influence to make them accept his plan. 他用尽一切影响力使他们接受他的计划。 2. He doesn\'t have to exert himself on my behalf. 他不必为我费那么大力气。 3. You have to exert more efforts if you want to catch up with your classmates. 你要想赶上你的同学的话,就得多花些功夫。 4. His teachings still exert a strong influence. 他的教导仍在产生巨大影响。', '过去式: exerted 过去分词: exerted 现在分词: exerting 第三人称单数: exerts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grammar', '[\'ɡræmər]', 'n.语法；文法', '1. That is not, properly speaking, a dictionary but a grammar book. 严格地说，那不是一本字典，而是一本语法书。 2. I know nothing about Latin grammar. 我一点都不懂拉丁语法。 3. Why care for grammar as long as we are good? 只要我们没有错，为什么要关心文法? 4. Grammar is not that hard to reach. 文法也不是那么难以亲近.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('class', '[klæs]', 'n.等级；阶级；阶层；班级；课；[生]纲；<口>出色的风度 v.分类', '1. I wouldn\'t put him in the same class as Verdi. 我没把他看作是与维迪一个级别的。 2. All of us are working class. 我们都是工人阶级。 3. They are the leading class in our country. 在我们国家,他们是领导阶级。 4. We were both in the same class. 那时我们在同一个班。 5. Immigrant workers were classed as resident aliens. 移民来的工人已归入外侨类。', '过去式: classed 过去分词: classed 现在分词: classing 第三人称单数: classes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mixture', '[\'mɪkstʃər]', 'n.混合；混合物', '1. You need a spoon to beat the mixture smooth. 你需要用一把调羹来搅均混合液。 2. Air is a mixture, not a compound of gases. 空气是气体的混合物，不是化合物。 3. The bottom layer is a mixture of sand and clay. 最下面的一层是沙和泥的混合物。 4. She trickles oil into the mixture. 她把油一点点地注入混合物中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('facility', '[fə\'sɪləti]', 'n.设备；设施；才能；资质；灵巧；熟练', '1. The college has excellent sporting facilities. 这所学院有极好的体育设备。 2. There are few recreational facilities in our school. 我们学校里几乎没有什么娱乐设施。 3. He has great facility in learning languages. 他很有学习语言的才能。 4. I learn to use with more and more facility the pencil, brush, and graver. 我学会越来越灵巧地运用铅笔、画笔和雕刻刀。', '名词复数: facilities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skull', '[skʌl]', 'n.头骨；骷髅头', '1. Have scientists found Mozart\'s skull? 科学家们已经找到了莫扎特的头骨吗? 2. Her skull had been fractured by two separate blows. 她的头骨在两次重击下骨折。 3. They stamped a skull and crossbones on the label of poisonous drug. 他们在毒药标签上打上骷髅图。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slippery', '[\'slɪpəri]', 'adj.滑的；狡猾的；不可靠的', '1. A wet road is usually slippery. 潮湿的路往往是滑的。 2. The road was slippery after the rain. 下雨之后道路很滑。 3. Don\'t lend any money to that slippery person. 不要借钱给那个狡猾的家伙。 4. The England striker says the slippery Portuguese winker got him sent off in Saturday\'s World Cup clash. 英格兰前锋说这个狡猾的葡萄牙人在周六的比赛中迫使自己下场后挤眉弄眼。', '比较级: slipperier 最高级: slipperiest 名词: slipperiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('denote', '[dɪ\'noʊt]', 'vt.表示；象征', '1. A smile often denotes pleasure and friendship. 微笑常常表示高兴和友善。 2. These nouns denote a state of joyful exuberance. 这些名词都指示洋溢着欢乐的状态。 3. Dark clouds denote a coming storm. 黑云表明风暴要来临。 4. We often denote danger by red letters. 我们常常用红字表示危险。', '形容词: denotable 过去式: denoted 过去分词: denoted 现在分词: denoting 第三人称单数: denotes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('awful', '[\'ɔːfl]', 'adj.糟糕的；可怕的；充满敬畏的；难受的 adv.极其', '1. It would be awful if he found out the truth. 如果他发现了真相，那就糟了。 2. I left Harvard with no real awareness of the awful inequities in the world. 当我离开哈佛时,我并没真正有意识到这个世界存在着可怕的不平等现象。 3. He seemed to be very awful while serving the famous actress. 他在招待那位著名的女演员时,看上去非常的敬畏。 4. I feel awful about not inviting her. 没有邀请她,我感到很内疚。 5. These weeks is an awful long time to wait. 这几个星期真的是一段极其漫长的等待时间啊。', '副词: awfully 名词: awfulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('liner', '[\'laɪnər]', 'n.班轮；班机；邮轮 n.衬里', '1. The liner is in dock for a refit. 班轮正在船坞修理。 2. The liner has been refitted from stem to stern. 那艘班轮已经全面整修。 3. Hundreds died when the liner went down. 班轮沉没时，有数百人罹难。 4. Hundreds of small craft accompany the liner into harbour. 数百只小艇随同这艘班轮驶入港湾。 5. The liner of my coat was broken. 我的外套衬里破了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('removal', '[rɪ\'muːvl]', 'n.移动；搬迁；除去；开除', '1. The removal of a neutron from the system is indicated by the head of an arrow. 用箭头表示一个中子从这个系统中的移动。 2. We haven\'t told our friends about our removal to London. 我们还没有告诉我们的朋友我们搬家到伦敦了。 3. Our ultimate objective is the removal of all nuclear weapons. 我们的最终目标是消除所有核武器。 4. Their removal is effected by aluminum and ferric salts. 用铁盐和铝盐能将其有效地除去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commute', '[kə\'mjuːt]', 'v.通勤；折换；减刑；改变；交换 n.乘车上下班', '1. Mary used to commute five miles from her home in the suburb. 玛丽过去每天从郊区的家里走五英里来上班。 2. They chose to commute equity into license agreements. 他们选择了将股权转换成许可协议。 3. Regular train travellers may commute a single monthly payment for daily tickets. 经常坐火车的人可以按每天的票价折换购买月票。 4. He seemed at times to be asking God to commute these penalties. 有时他好象还恳求上帝减轻惩罚。 5. Her commute to work will be easy. 她上下班交通会很方便。', '过去式: commuted 过去分词: commuted 现在分词: commuting 第三人称单数: commutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('entity', '[\'entəti]', 'n.实体；存在；本质', '1. A corporation is treated by the law as an entity. 法人在法律上被视为一个实体。 2. It describes the change in an entity\'s state. 它描述了一个实体的状态变化。', '名词复数: entities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intercourse', '[\'ɪntərkɔːrs]', 'n.交往；交流；性交', '1. There was close intercourse between them. 他们过往很密。 2. English is more widespread and more used in international intercourse than German. 英语在国际交往中比德语使用得更为广泛。 3. The whole intercourse was wordless, intense and close. 整个交流都是在默默无声中进行的，强烈而又亲密。 4. The magazine becomes a cultural medium of intercourse between the two peoples. 该杂志成为两民族间文化交流的媒介。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('notion', '[\'noʊʃn]', 'n.观念；概念；想法；主张', '1. State control is a very un-American notion. 实行国家控制是根本违背美国观念的。 2. They want a system based on the notions of personal equality and liberty. 他们想要基于人的平等﹑ 自由等概念的制度。 3. We had a notion that he was telling a lie. 我们当时的看法是他在说谎。 4. She dinged the notion into our ears. 她老是唠唠叨叨地跟我们讲那个想法。(或：她把那个想法反反复复地灌输给我们)。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('to', '[tə]', 'prep.对于；为了；(表示方向)到；向；(表示间接关系)给 adv.（表示方向）去；（门）关上', '1. This will be a great boost to the economy. 这对于经济发展将是一个巨大的促进。 2. We come here to see you . 我们来这里是为了看你。 3. Her dress reached down to her ankles. 她的连衣裙垂至脚踝。 4. This road leads to London. 这条路通向伦敦。 5. He is walking to and fro in the room. 他在房间内踱来踱去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extension', '[ɪk\'stenʃn]', 'n.延长；伸展；延期；扩充；观念发展；增强 n.电话分机；特别课程 n.[计]文件名', '1. This cord is not long enough! do you have an extension? 这条绳子不够长！你有长一点的吗？ 2. His leg was now capable of full extension. 他的腿现在能够伸展自如了。 3. He asked for an extension of his visa. 他申请延长签证有效期。 4. We built an extension to our house. 我们扩建了我家的房屋。 5. There are telephone extensions in every office. 每间办公室都有电话分机。 6. Method will only return one unique file name per file name extension. 方法对每个文件名扩展名只返回一个唯一文件名。', '形容词: extensional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('notify', '[\'noʊtɪfaɪ]', 'v.通知；报告；通告', '1. Please notify us of any change of address. 地址如有变动，请通知我们。 2. She notified us of the meeting. 她通知我们开会。 3. We\'ll notify her to draw up a contract. 我们将通知她起草一份合同。 4. They will notify her when to appear in court. 他们将通知她何时出庭。', '名词: notifier 过去式: notified 过去分词: notified 现在分词: notifying 第三人称单数: notifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yawn', '[jɔːn]', 'v.打呵欠；张开 n.呵欠；<口>乏味的人（事）', '1. His long boring story made me yawn. 他的冗长的故事听得我直打呵欠。 2. He closed the book, yawned, and went to bed. 他合起书, 打了个呵欠, 然后上床睡觉了。 3. The deep crevasse yawned at their feet. 他们脚下的冰川有一道深深的裂缝。 4. I gave a loud yawn, but he just kept on talking. 我大声打了个呵欠，可他还是不停地讲下去。', '名词: yawner 过去式: yawned 过去分词: yawned 现在分词: yawning 第三人称单数: yawns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('public', '[\'pʌblɪk]', 'adj.公众的；公共的；公开的 n.民众；公众；大众', '1. Changing public perception may take some time. 改变公众的看法需要一些时间。 2. The pension fund owns shares in several major public companies. 该养老基金在几家主要出售股份给公众的公司中均有股份。 3. The government decided to promote public welfare. 政府决定发展公共福利。 4. The town has its own public library and public gardens. 那城市有自己的公用图书馆和公园。 5. The area has been fenced from the public. 该地区为防止民众进出而围起来。', '名词: publicness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refuse', '[rɪ\'fjuːz]', 'v.拒绝 n.垃圾；废物', '1. I refuse to answer that question. 我不愿回答那个问题。 2. We were refused permission to enter. 我们被拒之门外。 3. There is a refuse dump out of the town. 镇外有个垃圾场。 4. The council is responsible for refuse collection. 市政局负责清除垃圾废物。', '名词: refuser 过去式: refused 过去分词: refused 现在分词: refusing 第三人称单数: refuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('draft', '[dræft]', 'n.草稿；草图；汇票；征兵 vt.起草；征兵；选秀 adj.酝酿中的', '1. He drew a draft of the car. 他画了一张汽车的草图。 2. He has drawn up the design draft. 他拟订了设计草图。 3. He drew a draft on a pad then began his formal work. 他在便笺簿上画了草图，然后就开始正式工作了。 4. I propose issuing a time draft for US $ 100,000. 我建议开具价值10万美元的远期汇票。 5. Who will draft the indictment? 谁将起草起诉状？ 6. The Authority may suggest any other proposal it thinks fit for inclusion into the draft corporate plan. 市建局可提议其认为适合包括在事务计划草案内的任何其他提案。', '过去式: drafted 过去分词: drafted 现在分词: drafting 第三人称单数: drafts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alter', '[\'ɔːltər]', 'v.改变；更改；阉割；切除卵巢', '1. But nothing can alter the facts. 但任何东西也改变不了这些事实。 2. Alter Current Boot Record Serial Number. 更改当前引导纪录序列号。 3. Marshaling the structure can transform the layout and alter the offset. 封送结构可转换布局并更改偏移量。', '过去式: altered 过去分词: altered 现在分词: altering 第三人称单数: alters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('telegram', '[\'telɪɡræm]', 'n. 电报 vt. 向 ... 发电报', '1. The telegram asked for an instant reply. 这封电报要求立即回覆。 2. I received a telegram from my father. 我收到父亲的一封电报。 3. How much will the telegram cost? 发电报要多少钱？ 4. We\'d send a telegram to order the correspondent bank to advise and pay the money to the remittee. 我们要发电报给那儿的代理行，经它去通知收款人，并付给收款人汇款金额。', '过去式: telegrammed 过去分词: telegrammed 现在分词: telegramming 第三人称单数: telegrams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bag', '[bæɡ]', 'n.袋；袋状物；包；一袋的量 vt.把 ... 装进袋子；使膨胀；猎杀 vi.（如袋子般）松垂', '1. He lost his travelling bag when he crossed the desert. 他在穿越沙漠的时候丢失了他的旅行袋。 2. The boxer\'s fist thumped into the punching bag. 拳师猛击吊袋。 3. He put his bag on the luggage rack. 他把包放在行李架上。 4. The cat had not been fed for weeks and was just a bag of bones. 那只猫已有几个星期没喂食了，简直成了皮包骨。 5. They bagged the potatoes to sell them. 他们把土豆装入袋中出售。', '名词: bagful 过去式: bagged 过去分词: bagged 现在分词: bagging 第三人称单数: bags');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abundance', '[ə\'bʌndəns]', 'n.丰富；充裕', '1. At the party there is food and drink in abundance. 宴会中有丰富的食物和饮料。 2. This country has an abundance of natural resources. 这个国家拥有丰富的天然资源。 3. There was an abundance of corn last year. 去年玉米丰收。 4. Carpets are available in abundance. 可供地毯货源充足。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('encourage', '[ɪn\'kɜːrɪdʒ]', 'vt.鼓励；促进；支持', '1. Her success encouraged me to try the same thing. 她的成功鼓励我尝试做同样的事。 2. Her parents encouraged her in her studies. 她的父母鼓励她好好学习。 3. He aims to encourage mutual understanding. 他的目的在于增进相互了解。 4. Broadband support flat salary structure, to encourage their staff to study hard. 宽带薪酬支持扁平型结构，鼓励员工努力学习。', '名词: encourager 过去式: encouraged 过去分词: encouraged 现在分词: encouraging 第三人称单数: encourages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('courage', '[\'kɜːrɪdʒ]', 'n.勇气；胆量', '1. He showed remarkable courage when he faced the danger. 他在面对危险的时候表现出非凡的勇气。 2. I don\'t think I have the courage to tell him the bad news. 我觉得我没有勇气告诉他这个坏消息。 3. Do you have the courage to go bungee jumping? 你有胆量玩蹦极跳吗?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('universe', '[\'juːnɪvɜːrs]', 'n.宇宙；万物；世界', '1. The universe exists in space. 宇宙存在于太空。 2. The depth of the universe is immeasurable. 宇宙无限深广。 3. The Earth is only one of the numerous planets in the universe. 地球只是宇宙中众多星球中的一个。 4. Man is the soul of the universe. 人是万物之灵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spring', '[sprɪŋ]', 'n.春天；春季；弹簧；弹力；跳；泉水；源头 v.跳；弹；快速站起；突然提出；触发捕捉器；(使)裂开；爆炸；释放；涌出；生长；出现；耸立；(风)开始吹', '1. Spring is here. 春天来了。 2. It can be quite windy there, especially in spring. 那里有时容易刮风,特别在春季。 3. When the box was opened, the spring jumped out. 盒子一打开，弹簧就绷出来了。 4. There is too much spring in this bed. 这张床太有弹性。 5. The cat crouched ready to spring. 那猫躬起背准备跳。', '过去式: sprang/sprung 过去分词: sprung 现在分词: springing 第三人称单数: springs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('example', '[ɪɡ\'zæmpl]', 'n.例子；榜样；举例；警告 vt.作为 ... 的示范', '1. It is a classic example of how not to design a new city centre. 这对设计新市中心是个最佳的反面教材。 2. This church is a classic example of medieval architecture. 这座教堂是中世纪建筑风格的典型实例。 3. Her diligence has set an example to the others. 她的勤奋为其他人树立了榜样。 4. Comrade LeiFeng set us a good example to emulate. 雷峰同志为我们树立了可供效仿的榜样。 5. He can set a good example for Chinese coaches. 他可以为中国教练做好的示范。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('candy', '[\'kændi]', 'n.糖果 v.用糖煮；使结晶为砂糖', '1. The greedy little boy ate all the candy at the party. 那个贪吃的小男孩把宴会上所有的糖果都吃光了。 2. The mother distributed candy among children. 母亲给孩子们发糖果。 3. They candy fruit in autumn every year. 他们每年秋天都做蜜饯水果。 4. The honey will candy in half an hour. 再过半个小时蜂蜜就会凝结起来。', '名词复数: candies 过去式: candied 过去分词: candied 现在分词: candying 第三人称单数: candies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prove', '[pruːv]', 'v.证明；检验；结果是；发酵', '1. There wasn\'t enough evidence to prove him guilty. 没有充分的证据证明他有罪。 2. He has proved his courage in the battle. 他已在这场战斗中证明了自己的勇气。 3. The students are asked to prove the purity of copper. 要求学生们检验铜的纯度。 4. Leave the dough to prove for half an hour. 让面团发酵半小时。', '形容词: provable 副词: provably 名词: provability 过去式: proved/proven 过去分词: proved/proven 现在分词: proving 第三人称单数: proves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drastic', '[\'dræstɪk]', 'adj.激烈的；重大的；极端的', '1. His view brings a drastic argument. 他的观点引起激烈的争论。 2. Drastic measures were taken to combat inflation. 已采取激烈措施对付通货膨胀。 3. Talk to me before you do anything drastic. 你采取任何重大行动之前要跟我谈谈。 4. Our budget needs drastic revision. 我们的预算需作重大修改。', '副词: drastically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('breathe', '[briːð]', 'vi.呼吸 vt.轻声说；流露（自信等感情）；注入', '1. Fish cannot breathe out of water. 鱼离开水就不能呼吸。 2. It is difficult to breathe at these altitudes. 在这些高的地方很难呼吸。 3. We breathe through the nasal passage. 我们通过鼻腔呼吸。 4. Promise me you won\'t breathe a word of this to anyone. 答应我别将此事泄漏给任何人。', '形容词: breathable 过去式: breathed 过去分词: breathed 现在分词: breathing 第三人称单数: breathes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('not', '[nɑːt]', 'adv.不；没有；并非', '1. I\'m not really sure. 我不太清楚。 2. It\'s not your fault. 不是你的错。 3. We are not teachers. 我们不是老师。 4. They will not agree. 他们不会同意。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oven', '[\'ʌvn]', 'n.烤箱；烤炉', '1. The bread is baking in the oven. 烤箱里正在烤面包。 2. It is like an oven in here; please open the window. 这里热得像火炉,请把窗户打开。 3. The bread is fresh out of the oven. 面包刚出炉。 4. The cook went to see the cake left in the oven. 炊事员去照看炉子里的蛋糕了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flatter', '[\'flætər]', 'v.奉承；恭维；取悦；显得好看', '1. My boss likes it when we flatter him. 我的老板喜欢我们奉承他。 2. Friends who flatter you to your face are not true friends. 凡是当面奉承你的朋友不是真朋友。 3. He flattered her about her cooking. 他恭维她的烹调手艺。 4. It\'s impossible for you to ask a girl to teach you how to flatter another. 你不可能让一个女孩教你如何取悦另一个女孩。', '副词: flatteringly 名词: flatterer 过去式: flattered 过去分词: flattered 现在分词: flattering 第三人称单数: flatters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sarcastic', '[sɑːr\'kæstɪk]', 'adj.讽刺的', '1. He chopped in with a sarcastic remark. 他突然插进一句讽刺的话。 2. I felt completely squashed by her sarcastic comment. 她冷嘲热讽把我噎得一句话都说不出来。 3. I could see from her expression that his sarcastic comments had hit home. 从她的表情中我可以看出他那些挖苦人的话已经触及她的痛处。', '副词: sarcastically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('premium', '[\'priːmiəm]', 'n.额外费用；奖金；保险费 n.(商)溢价 adj.高价的；优质的', '1. Who will pay the premium for the risk of breakage? 加保破碎险的费用由谁负担? 2. A premium of 2 percent is paid on long-term investments. 对投资期限较长者可获百分之二的奖励。 3. He\'s had to lay his car up for he can\'t afford the insurance premiums. 因付不起保险费他只得把汽车搁置起来。 4. Shares are selling at a premium. 股票溢价出售。 5. People are prepared to pay premium prices for quality products. 人们已经作好为优质产品花费更多的准备。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('vowel', '[\'vaʊəl]', 'n.母音；元音', '1. The student was practising making a new vowel sound . 那个学生在练习一个新母音的发音。 2. A vowel can form a syllable by itself. 元音能单独构成音节。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pathetic', '[pə\'θetɪk]', 'adj.可怜的；不足的；感伤的；悲哀的', '1. We saw the pathetic sight of starving children. 我们看到挨饿的儿童悲惨可怜的样子。 2. She dances well, but as a singer, she is pathetic. 她跳舞跳得好，但唱歌就差劲了。 3. God! The freshmen are pathetic this year! 天啊！今年的大一新生什么也不懂！ 4. I never heard anything that sounded so pathetic. 我从未听说过如此悲伤的事了。', '副词: pathetically 异体字: pathetical');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('swim', '[swɪm]', 'v.游泳 n.游泳', '1. Let\'s go swimming. 咱们游泳去。 2. She\'s teaching the children to swim. 她正在教孩子们游泳。 3. I used to swim all the year round. 过去我一年四季都游泳。 4. I like to swim, but I\'m not a very good swimmer. 我喜欢游泳，可是我游得并不好。 5. He went down to the beach for a swim. 他去海滩游泳了。', '形容词: swimmable 名词: swimmer 过去式: swam 过去分词: swum 现在分词: swimming 第三人称单数: swims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('leak', '[liːk]', 'v.渗；漏；泄露 n.漏洞；泄露', '1. Water had started to leak into the cellar. 水已开始渗入地下室。 2. The kitchen roof is apt to leak when it rains. 厨房的屋顶下雨时容易漏雨。 3. The details were supposed to be secret but somehow leaked out. 这些细节原属秘密，可是不知怎么给泄露出去了。 4. There is a leak in the roof. 屋顶有一个漏洞。', '名词: leaker 过去式: leaked 过去分词: leaked 现在分词: leaking 第三人称单数: leaks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stimulate', '[\'stɪmjuleɪt]', 'vt.刺激；激励；鼓舞 vi.起刺激作用', '1. Light stimulates plant growth. 光会刺激植物生长。 2. Alcohol stimulates the action of the heart. 酒刺激心脏的活动。 3. Praise always stimulates him to further efforts. 一表扬他就能激励他更加努力。 4. I\'m trying to stimulate him to study harder. 我试图激励他更加用功读书。', '形容词: stimulative 副词: stimulatingly 名词: stimulater 过去式: stimulated 过去分词: stimulated 现在分词: stimulating 第三人称单数: stimulates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gulf', '[ɡʌlf]', 'n.海湾；鸿沟 vt.吞没', '1. The gulf extends northward. 海湾向北方延伸。 2. The Gulf War has sapped Iraqi vitality badly. 海湾战争使伊拉克大伤元气。 3. Thousands of ships enwombed in the gulf of mexico. 数千艘的船深藏在墨西哥海湾中。 4. Between him and Mr Smith there was a great gulf fixed. 他与史密斯之间有一道永远不可逾越的鸿沟。', '过去式: gulfed 过去分词: gulfed 现在分词: gulfing 第三人称单数: gulfs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('land', '[lænd]', 'n.陆地；国土；土地 v.靠岸；着陆；跌落地面；得到；使靠岸；使着陆', '1. We are glad to be on land again. 我们很高兴又踏上陆地了。 2. The river passes through our land. 这条河流经我们的国土 3. The land is laid down with red or white clover. 这块土地种上了红花和白花苜蓿。 4. This land was reclaimed from the sea. 这块土地是填海开垦出来的。 5. The ship landed safely in the end. 船最后平安靠岸了。', '过去式: landed 过去分词: landed 现在分词: landing 第三人称单数: lands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aim', '[eɪm]', 'n.目标；对准；枪法 vt.瞄准；针对 vi.瞄准；旨在；致力', '1. What is your aim in life? 你的生活目标是什么？ 2. The aim of the policy is the preservation of peace. 这一政策旨在维护和平。 3. Take careful aim at the target before firing. 开火之前仔细瞄准目标。 4. The shooter\'s aim was perfect. 射击者的枪法棒极了 5. The policeman aimed his gun at the fugitive. 警察用枪对准逃犯。 6. You have to aim at the centre of the target. 你得瞄准靶心。', '过去式: aimed 过去分词: aimed 现在分词: aiming 第三人称单数: aims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loaf', '[loʊf]', 'n.（一条）面包；块 vi.游手好闲；虚掷光阴', '1. That small loaf won\'t go far among this large family! 那一小条面包全家人吃不了多久的。 2. He bought a loaf of bread. 他买了一大块奶酪。 3. He used to loaf about and ultimately took to drink. 他过去终日游手好闲，最终沉溺于酗酒。 4. Those who loaf all day and do nothing are social parasites. 饱食终日，无所事事的人是社会上的寄生虫。', '名词复数: loaves 过去式: loafed 过去分词: loafed 现在分词: loafing 第三人称单数: loafs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ignore', '[ɪɡ\'nɔːr]', 'vt.忽视；不理；不顾', '1. If you ignore your diet, trouble will follow. 如果你忽视自己的饮食，必然会遇到麻烦 2. I agree in principle, but we can\'t ignore the differences. 我原则上同意,但我们不能忽视这些差异。 3. The wisest course would be to ignore it. 上上策是不予理睬。 4. We could ignore him and go direct to the chairman, but we\'d be skating on very thin ice. 我们可以不理会他而直接去找主席，但那样做我们就如履薄冰了。', '形容词: ignorable 名词: ignorer 过去式: ignored 过去分词: ignored 现在分词: ignoring 第三人称单数: ignores');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relay', '[\'riːleɪ]', 'vt.转播；转达；中继；接力；接替 n.继电器；接力赛；替班', '1. Images of the war were relayed around the world. 世界各地转播了战争的图像。 2. I will relay your opinion to the headmaster. 我愿把你的意见转告校长。 3. The Relay Agent could not start up its main thread. 中继代理无法启动其主线程。 4. Frame Relay Connection and Traffic Flow Control. 帧中继连接和流量控制。 5. This relay connects one input to one output. 该继电器将一个输入连接到一个输出。', '过去式: relayed 过去分词: relayed 现在分词: relaying 第三人称单数: relays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fare', '[fer]', 'n.车费；路费；乘客；食物 vi.过活；进展；进食；旅行；行走', '1. Let me go shares with you in the taxi fare. 我和你分摊计程车费吧。 2. She didn\'t have enough money for the bus fare. 她的钱不够付车费。 3. He didn\'t have enough money to pay his train fare. 他没有足够的钱来付火车费。 4. The normal return fare to New York is fifty-six. 去纽约的来回票标准价是56元。 5. How would I fare in a strange city? 在一个陌生的城市里，我怎么度日呢?', '名词: farer 过去式: fared 过去分词: fared 现在分词: faring 第三人称单数: fares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('noisy', '[\'nɔɪzi]', 'adj.喧闹的；嘈杂的；吵闹的', '1. I prefer the quiet countryside to the noisy cities. 我喜欢安静的乡村胜过喧闹的城市。 2. He was notorious for his noisy parties in the town. 因为他搞了多次喧闹的晚会，所以他在镇上声名狼藉。 3. I have got accustomed to noisy sound. 我已习惯于嘈杂声音。 4. These noisy conditions aren\'t really conducive to concentrated work. 这嘈杂的环境实在不利于专心工作。', '副词: noisily 比较级: noisier 最高级: noisiest 名词: noisiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('champion', '[\'tʃæmpiən]', 'n.拥护者；冠军；优胜者；勇士 vt.拥护；保卫；为 ... 而斗争', '1. He is a champion of women\'s rights. 他是妇女权利的卫士. 2. He is the undisputed champion. 他是无可争辩的冠军。 3. He is a champion at writing familiar essays. 他是写小品文的好手。 4. Every absurdity have a champion to defend it. 任何谬论都拥有拥护它的斗士。 5. He is forced to champion unpopular causes. 他被迫去支持一些不得人心的事业。', '过去式: championed 过去分词: championed 现在分词: championing 第三人称单数: champions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pant', '[pænt]', 'n.喘息；悸动 vt.气喘吁吁地说 vi.渴望；喘息 (复数）pants：n.裤子', '1. He was panting with desire for her. 他拼命地追求他。 2. Instead, a dog has to pant to keep cool. 一只狗必须通过气喘来保持凉块。', '副词: pantingly 过去式: panted 过去分词: panted 现在分词: panting 第三人称单数: pants');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('apology', '[ə\'pɑːlədʒi]', 'n.道歉；辩解；<口>勉强的代用品', '1. I demand an apology. 我要求道歉。 2. Please accept my apology. 请接受我的道歉。 3. He made a contrite apology. 他深表懊悔地致歉。 4. In my judgement, we should accept their apology. 依我看，我们应该接受他们的道歉。', '名词复数: apologies 动词: apologize');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plane', '[pleɪn]', 'n.飞机；水平；平面 n.刨子 n.悬铃木 adj.平的；飞机的 vt.磨平；刨 vi.（鸟、飞机）滑翔', '1. The plane flew high above. 飞机高高地在上空飞。 2. The plane circled the airport before landing. 飞机在着陆之前在机场上空盘旋。 3. Keep your work on a high plane. 使你的工作保持在高水平上。 4. Let\'s keep the conversation on a friendly plane. 让我们友好地谈话。 5. The carpenter evened a board with a plane. 那位木工用刨刨平一块木板。 6. The bark of plane trees peels off regularly. 悬铃木的树皮到时候就脱落。 7. The dense fog delayed the plane\'s start. 浓雾延误了飞机的起飞。 8. He has planed the plank smooth. 他已把木板刨平。 9. Seagulls planed over the cliffs. 海鸥在翱翔,飞过了悬崖。', '名词: planeness 过去式: planed 过去分词: planed 现在分词: planing 第三人称单数: planes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chance', '[tʃæns]', 'n.可能性；机会；偶然性 v.偶然发生；碰巧；冒 ... (的险)', '1. That would be a daunting task with little chance of success. 那样做的话任务过于艰巨,且成功的可能性微乎其微。 2. Is there any chance of getting tickets for tonight\'s performance? 有可能得到今晚演出的票吗? 3. Please give me a chance to explain. 请给我个机会让我解释一下。 4. I never miss a chance of playing football. 我从不错过踢足球的机会。 5. If it should chance to rain we\'ll take a taxi home. 万一要下雨的话，我们就乘出租车回家。', '过去式: chanced 过去分词: chanced 现在分词: chancing 第三人称单数: chances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('irritate', '[\'ɪrɪteɪt]', 'v.激怒；使疼痛或发炎', '1. His letter irritated me a little. 他的信使我有点恼怒。 2. Don\'t irritate her, she\'s on a short fuse today. 别惹她，她今天动不动就发火。 3. Wool irritates my skin. 毛织物会使我的皮肤过敏。 4. Insect bites irritate your skin. 虫子叮疼了你的皮肤。', '副词: irritatingly 名词: irritator 过去式: irritated 过去分词: irritated 现在分词: irritating 第三人称单数: irritates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ours', '[ɑːrz]', 'pron.我们的', '1. Your house is much bigger than ours. 你们的房子比我们的大多了。 2. Their opinion jarred with ours. 他们的意见与我们不一致。 3. Ours is small. 我们的是小的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('he', '[hi:]', 'pron.他；任何人 n.男人；雄性动物', '1. He is a teacher. 他是教师。 2. It was not until he came that I left. 直到他来我才离开。 3. He beat the other runners by a margin of ten seconds. 他比其他运动员早10秒钟到达终点。 4. Everybody knows what he wants. 人人都知道自己想要的是什么。 5. What a sweet puppy! Is it a he or a she? 多可爱的小狗哇！是公的还是母的?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accordance', '[ə\'kɔːrdns]', 'n.一致；符合；授予；给予', '1. He acted in accordance with his beliefs. 他按照自己的信念行事。 2. I shall be glad if you will forward fifty ton of coal, in accordance with your sample. 请按照贵公司提供的样品，供应我司50吨煤炭，谢谢。 3. The mayor must make policies in accordance with the bill passed in the Congress. 市长要根据议会的议案来制定政策。 4. Install in accordance with the local codes. 安装方法要符合当地规程的要求。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('willing', '[\'wɪlɪŋ]', 'adj.愿意的；心甘情愿的', '1. Are you willing to help? 你愿意帮忙吗？ 2. I don\'t know whether he is willing to come. 我不知道他是否愿意来。 3. The spirit is willing but the flesh is weak. 心有余而力不足。 4. I\'d like to buy your house if you are willing to sell it. 如果你愿意卖的话，我想买你的房子。', '副词: willingly 名词: willingness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trifle', '[\'traɪfl]', 'n.琐事；少量 v.浪费；玩弄', '1. I do not want to make a fuss over such a trifle. 我不想为这种小事大惊小怪。 2. They had an altercation about a trifle. 他们为一点小事争吵起来。 3. He told her not to pester him with trifles. 他告诉她别拿些琐事来烦他。 4. I have only a trifle of wine left. 我只剩下一点点酒了。 5. Don\'t trifle away your time on curio hunting. 别把时间都浪费在搜集古玩上面。', '名词: trifler 过去式: trifled 过去分词: trifled 现在分词: trifling 第三人称单数: trifles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comment', '[\'kɑːment]', 'n.注释；评论；闲话 v.评论；注释', '1. The comment is recorded in the event log. 此注释将记录在事件日志中。 2. He made no comments on our proposal. 他对我们的建议没有作评论。 3. Her strange behavior caused a good deal of comment. 她的反常行为引起了不少闲话。 4. He commented that it was an excellent film. 他评论这电影很精彩。', '过去式: commented 过去分词: commented 现在分词: commenting 第三人称单数: comments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fracture', '[\'fræktʃər]', 'n.破碎；骨折 vt.破碎；破裂 vi.断裂', '1. A fellow team member says it was a clean fracture without complications. 一位队友表示这只是纯粹的锁骨破碎，没有任何并发症。 2. He had several injuries, including three fractures. 他多处受伤，其中三处骨折。 3. If you sneeze too hard, you can fracture a rib. 打喷嚏太用力的话肋骨可能会骨折。 4. Many people predicted that the party would fracture and split. 很多人预言该党将分崩离析。 5. Her leg fractured in two places. 她的腿有两处骨折。', '过去式: fractured 过去分词: fractured 现在分词: fracturing 第三人称单数: fractures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('calorie', '[\'kæləri]', 'n.卡；卡路里(热量单位) =calory.', '1. The calorie is a historical relic. 卡是历史的遗迹。 2. The calorie content in this ice cream is very high. 这种冰激凌的卡路里含量很高。 3. Diving can be as calorie consuming as you would like it to be. 潜水可以尽可能多地消耗卡路里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assure', '[ə\'ʃʊr]', 'vt.使确信；使放心；确保', '1. Her success as an actress was now assured. 她当演员很成功，已毋庸置疑了。 2. They tried to assure him of their willingness to work. 他们尽力使他相信他们乐意工作。 3. I can assure you that your son will be happy here. 我可以向你保证，你儿子在这里会很快乐的。 4. They were assured that everything possible was being done. 已经向他们保证，凡是可能做的都做到了。', '形容词: assurable 名词: assurer 过去式: assured 过去分词: assured 现在分词: assuring 第三人称单数: assures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('monthly', '[\'mʌnθli]', 'adj.每月的；一个月有效的；每月发生的 adv.每月；按月 n.月刊 n.(复数）monthlies:月经', '1. My monthly income was just over 200 pounds. 我每月的收入是200多磅。 2. Please show me your monthly bus pass. 请出示公共汽车月票。 3. His boss told him to be present at the monthly meeting. 他的老板要求他参加月会。 4. The meeting will be held monthly. 这种会议每月召开一次。 5. I think this magazine is a monthly. 我认为这本杂志是月刊。', '名词复数: monthlies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sell', '[sel]', 'v.出售；卖', '1. Her name will help to sell the film. 有她的名字，这部影片就卖座。 2. The group\'s record has sold millions. 他们的唱片已经售出了千千万万张了。 3. I\'d like to buy your house if you are willing to sell it. 如果你愿意卖的话，我想买你的房子。 4. Are artists who work in advertising selling themselves? 艺术家做广告是不是作践自己？', '形容词: sellable 过去式: sold 过去分词: sold 现在分词: selling 第三人称单数: sells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drive', '[draɪv]', 'vt.开车；驱赶；迫使 n.驾车；驱使；推进力；路；快车道；街；[计]驱动器', '1. He is too little to drive a car. 他太小了,不能开车。 2. Don\'t drink and drive. 别喝了酒开车。 3. They got a cat to drive out the mice. 他们找到一只猫来驱赶老鼠。 4. A man driven by jealousy is capable of anything. 嫉妒心可使人什么都做得出来。 5. We went for a drive in the afternoon. 我们下午开车出去兜风。', '形容词: drivable 名词: drivability 过去式: drove 过去分词: driven 现在分词: driving 第三人称单数: drives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tobacco', '[tə\'bækoʊ]', 'n.烟草', '1. A high amount of money is spent on tobacco every year. 每年都要花费大量金钱在烟草上。 2. It\'s forbidden to sell tobacco to children under 16. 禁止向16岁以下的儿童出售烟草。 3. His breath reeked of tobacco. 他口中带有烟草的臭味。 4. Tobacco and alcoholic drinks are taxed heavily in their country. 烟酒在他们的国家都被课以重税。', '名词复数: tobaccos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('split', '[splɪt]', 'v.分裂；将…分成若干部分；分摊；分离；劈开；裂开；<俚>离开 n.劈开；裂口；分裂；一份；水果冰淇淋 adj.分裂的；意见分歧的', '1. The party split into petty factions. 该党分裂成若干小派系。 2. The vote split the Labour Party. 那场选举使工党分裂了。 3. She split the class into groups of four. 她按四人一组把全班分成若干小组。 4. The arrow just split the apple in half. 箭把苹果分成两半。 5. Frost caused the split in the rock. 霜冻使岩石裂了一条缝。 6. They believe the killer has a split personality. 他们认为这个凶手人格分裂。', '名词: splitter 过去式: split 过去分词: split 现在分词: splitting 第三人称单数: splits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('define', '[dɪ\'faɪn]', 'v.规定；限定；定义；解释', '1. We should clearly define the scope of our research. 我们应该明确规定我们的研究范围。 2. The bank needs to define and delegate the responsibilities related to the various aspects of its marketing programme. 银行必须规定并授予与营销计划有关的各项职权。 3. The dependent claim shall,by additional technical features,further define the claim which it refers to. 从属权利要求应当用附加的技术特征，对引用的权利要求作进一步限定。 4. The section defines the extent of application of the Act. 该条款用来限定该法令的适用范围。', '形容词: definable 副词: definably 名词: definability 过去式: defined 过去分词: defined 现在分词: defining 第三人称单数: defines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('despite', '[dɪ\'spaɪt]', 'prep.尽管；不管 n.憎恨；轻视', '1. Despite old age, she is still learning to drive. 尽管年事已高,她还在学开车。 2. Despite all our efforts we still lost the game. 尽管我们尽了全力，我们还是输掉了比赛。 3. He came to the meeting despite his illness. 尽管生病，他还是来参加会议。 4. She managed despite everything to preserve her sense of humour. 她不管遇到什么情况都竭力保持着幽默感。 5. The statesman scoffed at the despites from his political enemy. 这位政治家对政敌的攻击嗤之以鼻。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hurry', '[\'hɜːri]', 'v.匆忙；催促；赶紧 n.匆忙；仓促；急忙', '1. She hurried to the airport. 她匆匆赶往机场。 2. He picked up his bag and hurried off along the platform. 他拿起提包沿着站台匆忙地走了。 3. Don\'t let anyone hurry you into making a decision. 不要在任何人的催促下匆促作出决定。 4. We\'d better hurry to the station by taxi to catch the train. 为了赶上火车,我们最好赶紧乘出租车去车站。 5. In his hurry, his bike ran against a tree. 匆忙中,他的自行车撞树上了。', '名词: hurrier 名词复数: hurries 过去式: hurried 过去分词: hurried 现在分词: hurrying 第三人称单数: hurries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tackle', '[\'tækl]', 'v.处理；对付；阻截(对方球员)；与…交涉 n.滑车；用具；铲球；(美式足球)拦截手', '1. Can you suggest how we might tackle the problem? 我们怎样处理这问题，你能给出个主意吗? 2. I suggested to him that we should tackle the problem another way. 我向他建议我们用另一种方式处理这个问题。 3. I\'ll tackle the boss for a raise. 我将与老板交涉要求增加薪水。 4. If Bill is late again I will tackle him about it . 如果彼尔再迟到的话，我就得和他开诚布公地谈谈了。 5. The cupboard was stuffed with old fishing tackle. 小橱里塞满了旧的钓鱼用具。', '名词: tackler 过去式: tackled 过去分词: tackled 现在分词: tackling 第三人称单数: tackles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inspire', '[ɪn\'spaɪər]', 'vt.鼓舞；激发；产生；赋予...灵感 vi.吸入', '1. We\'re trying to inspire him with confidence. 我们在努力鼓舞他的自信心。 2. The sight inspired him with nostalgia. 这景象激起了他的怀旧之情。 3. The failure inspired him to greater efforts. 失败激发他作更大的努力。 4. You inspire me with admiration. 你使我产生爱慕之心。', '名词: inspirer 过去式: inspired 过去分词: inspired 现在分词: inspiring 第三人称单数: inspires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('take', '[teɪk]', 'v.拿；取；执行；需要；接受；理解；修(课程)；花费；吃（喝）；认为；搭乘 n.拿取；取得物', '1. Please take the trash to the garbage can. 请将垃圾拿到垃圾筒去。 2. Take money from the bank when needed. 需要时,把钱从银行里取出来。 3. We are ready to take your order. 我们随时准备执行您的命令。 4. It takes a lot of money to live in that city. 要住在那个城市需要花不少钱。 5. Love includes gives and takes. 爱情包含着给予和索取。', '形容词: takable 过去式: took 过去分词: taken 现在分词: taking 第三人称单数: takes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ingenious', '[ɪn\'dʒiːniəs]', 'adj.机灵的；精巧的；有独创性的', '1. The ingenious boy made a radio set for himself. 这个聪明的男孩自己做了一台收音机。 2. He invented an ingenious excuse for being late. 他为迟到编造了一个巧妙的借口。 3. It was an intricate and ingenious system. 这是一个复杂而精致的体系。 4. I never heard anything more ingenious than your suggestion. 我从来没有听见过象你这样有独创性的提法。', '副词: ingeniously 名词: ingeniousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ordinary', '[\'ɔːrdneri]', 'adj.平凡的；普通的；平淡的', '1. I just want an ordinary car without the frills. 我只要一辆没有多余装饰的普通汽车。 2. Now electrical appliances have entered into ordinary families. 现在家用电器已经步入普通家庭。 3. It was an ordinary lunch of soup and a sandwich. 那是一顿平淡的午餐:一份汤,一份三明治。 4. The inside of the house is rather ordinary. 房子的内部相当平淡无奇。', '名词: ordinariness 名词复数: ordinaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brim', '[brɪm]', 'n.边；边缘 v.（装）满；（使）溢出', '1. He drank at the fountain\'s brim. 他醉在喷泉边。 2. The heart-shaped brim and brown velvet ribbon around the hat add a lovel accent. 心形边和褐色丝绒带周围的帽子向勒沃尔口音。 3. Nevertheless, the brim part of design is not very ideal. 不外，图案的边缘部门不是很完美。 4. With a dim triumph, she trims the swimming-suit rim at the swimming-pool brim. 她带着暗淡的喜悦在泳池边整理泳装的边缘。 5. The tea cup was filled to the brim. 茶杯满到杯子边了。', '过去式: brimmed 过去分词: brimmed 现在分词: brimming 第三人称单数: brims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shock', '[ʃɑːk]', 'n.震惊；震动；冲击；休克 v.使震惊；使震动；使受电击', '1. It gave me quite a shock to be told I was seriously ill. 听说我的病很严重，我吃了一惊。 2. His death was a great shock to us all. 他的死使我们大家都大为震惊。 3. We must take steps to prevent shock in the patient. 我们必须采取措施防止病人休克。 4. The violence and bad language in the program shocked many of the viewers. 节目中的暴力场面和难听的粗话使许多观众感到震惊。', '过去式: shocked 过去分词: shocked 现在分词: shocking 第三人称单数: shocks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clarify', '[\'klærəfaɪ]', 'vt.澄清；阐明；净化', '1. These brief remarks may serve to clarify the fact. 这些简要的评论可以澄清事实。 2. The teacher\'s explanation clarified the puzzling problem. 老师的说明澄清了困扰的问题。 3. Would you please clarify your question? 请你把你的问题说清楚好吗？ 4. She asked him to clarify what he meant. 她要他说清楚他是什么意思。', '名词: clarification 过去式: clarified 过去分词: clarified 现在分词: clarifying 第三人称单数: clarifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('erase', '[ɪ\'reɪs]', 'v.抹去；擦掉；[计算机]擦除', '1. She couldn\'t erase the incident from her memory. 她难以忘记那次事件。 2. I did my best to erase the event from my memory. 我尽全力从记忆中抹去这件事。 3. There is no way to erase what I have done. I am sorry. 我所做的事已是无法抹去了。我很抱歉。 4. You can erase pencil marks with a rubber. 你可以用橡皮擦掉铅笔记号。', '形容词: erasable 名词: erasability 过去式: erased 过去分词: erased 现在分词: erasing 第三人称单数: erases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whole', '[hoʊl]', 'adj.全部的；整体的；完整的 n.全部；整体；完整 adv.完全', '1. I had to listen to the whole nauseating story. 我不得不从头到尾听那令人作呕的故事。 2. The whole country was anxious for peace. 全国上下都渴望和平。 3. He is the prime mover in the whole matter. 他是整个事件的发起者。 4. He can say the whole of the English Bible by rote. 他能把整本英语《圣经》硬背出来。', '名词: wholeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('certificate', '[sər\'tɪfɪkət]', 'n.执照；证(明)书 vt.认可；批准；发证书给 ...', '1. The driver\'s certificate was suspended by the police. 这个司机的驾驶执照被警察吊销了。 2. He was afforded a certificate upon completion of his course of study. 他结业时被授予证书。 3. This is an accredited course and participants will receive 4.5 college credits and a world recognized Certificate of Nutrition upon completion. 本课程设学分制，完成课程的直销商可获国际认可大学学分，结业时将获颁发盖有美国大溪谷州立大学盖印的营养证书。 4. Bocog originally promised to issue a certificate of recognition to the participant in its global campaign whose slogan was adopted. 北京奥组委最初承诺，在全球征集活动中，一旦某一口号获选，将向口号的提出者颁发认可证书。', '形容词: certificatory 过去式: certificated 过去分词: certificated 现在分词: certificating 第三人称单数: certificates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tag', '[tæɡ]', 'n.标签；附属物；捉人游戏；谚语；名称 vt.连接；附以签条；尾随；添饰；指责 vi.紧随；尾随', '1. She peered at the tag to read the price. 她细看标签以看清价格。 2. The kids are playing tag over there. 小孩子正在那儿玩捉人游戏。 3. He would make a shot at a Latin tag. 他要尝试一下拉丁文短语。 4. A tag is another name for a media information attribute. 标记是媒体信息属性的另一个名称。 5. Will you tag these two together? 你把这两个连接在一起好吗? 6. If you\'re going to the cinema, do you mind if I tag along ? 你要是去看电影, 我也一起去行吗?', '过去式: tagged 过去分词: tagged 现在分词: tagging 第三人称单数: tags');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sane', '[seɪn]', 'adj.心智健全的；明智的', '1. A sane healthy mind can get momentarily off the rails. 正常健全的头脑也会一时失常。 2. It\'s hard to stay sane under such awful pressure. 处于这种可怕的压力之下，不疯才怪呢。 3. He made a sane choice. 他做了一个明智的选择。 4. She has a sane attitude toward diving and never goes too fast. 她对于跳水的态度很明智，从不操之过急。', '副词: sanely 比较级: saner 最高级: sanest 名词: saneness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whether', '[\'weðər]', 'conj.是否；不管；无论', '1. I\'m uncertain whether to go or not. 我不能肯定去还是不去。 2. His nationality isn\'t relevant to whether he\'s a good teacher. 他的国籍与他是否是位好老师无关。 3. Little does he care whether we live or die. 他一点也不管我们是死是活。 4. Air whether in the gaseous or liquid state is a fluid. 空气，无论是气态的还是液态的，都是一种流体。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enormous', '[ɪ\'nɔːrməs]', 'adj.巨大的；庞大的', '1. Long ago enormous animals lived on the earth. 很久以前，地球上生活着巨大的动物。 2. She stood alone on the enormous stage. 她孤零零地站在巨大的舞台上。 3. They overlooked the enormous risks involved. 他们忽略了暗含的巨大危险。 4. The sight of such an enormous crowd astonished us. 看到如此庞大的人群我惊讶万分。', '副词: enormously 名词: enormousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ceremony', '[\'serəmoʊni]', 'n.仪式；礼节；典礼', '1. The marriage ceremony took place in the church. 婚礼在教堂举行。 2. They hold a mystic religious ceremony. 他们举行了一个神秘的宗教仪式。 3. There\'s no need for ceremony between friends. 朋友之间不必拘礼. 4. What the old headmaster said at the graduation ceremony dwells in my mind. 老校长在毕业典礼上讲的话一直留在我的脑海里。', '名词复数: ceremonies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anyone', '[\'eniwʌn]', 'pron.任何人', '1. We dislike to have anyone patronize us. 我们不喜欢任何人对我们以恩人自居。 2. She never heeded anyone\'s warning. 她从不理会任何人的警告。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enclose', '[ɪn\'kloʊz]', 'vt.圈起；围住；附上；封入', '1. He enclosed the land with a hedge. 他用篱笆把地圈起来。 2. Farmers often enclose their land with hedges. 农夫们常用树篱将他们的地围起来。 3. With respect to your enquiry, I enclose an explanatory leaflet. 关于你的询问,兹附上有关说明资料。 4. We enclose a list showing our present availability. 兹附上我方现时可以供应的货单一张。', '异体字: inclose 过去式: enclosed 过去分词: enclosed 现在分词: enclosing 第三人称单数: encloses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ice', '[aɪs]', 'n.冰；糖霜；冰淇淋；冷淡；<俚>钻石 v.用冰裹；冰镇；结冰；制冷；涂糖霜', '1. The bird picked a hole in the ice with its beak. 那鸟在冰上啄出了一个洞。 2. The ice cracked as I stepped onto it. 我一踩冰就裂了。 3. The boy especially likes the ice on the cake. 那个男孩特别喜欢吃蛋糕上的糖霜。 4. She ordered a strawberry ice cream. 她要了一份草莓冰淇淋。 5. He must ice after every workout and game for about a half hour. 他必须在每次训练和比赛前用冰敷大约一个半小时。', '形容词: iceless 过去式: iced 过去分词: iced 现在分词: icing 第三人称单数: ices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commodity', '[kə\'mɑːdəti]', 'n.商品；日用品；有价值之物', '1. Coal is becoming a rare commodity. 煤正在成为一种稀缺商品。 2. In spite of the depression, the price of commodity is still high 尽管有些萧条,但商品的价格仍然很高。 3. The country is heavily dependent on its exports of agricultural commodities. 这个国家很大程度上依靠农产品的出口。 4. Time is our most valuable commodity. 时间是最有价值之物。', '名词复数: commodities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('baby', '[\'beɪbi]', 'n.婴儿；宝贝儿；孩子气的人 adj.婴儿的；小型的 vt.溺爱', '1. She gave birth to a fine healthy baby. 她生了一个健康漂亮的婴儿。 2. The mother rocked the baby to sleep in its cradle. 母亲摇动摇篮使婴儿入睡。 3. We\'ve turned the smallest bedroom into a nursery for our new baby. 我们已将最小的那间卧室改成新生婴儿的幼儿室。 4. Baby, come on, let\'s go home, I\'m tired. 宝贝儿，快点儿，我们回家吧，我累了。 5. Since 2001, organic baby food sales have jumped 63%. 从2001年以来,有机婴儿食品销售额已上升63%25。 6. Don\'t baby the boy. 别惯这孩子。', '形容词: babyish 比较级: babier 最高级: babiest 名词: babyhood 名词复数: babies 过去式: babied 过去分词: babied 现在分词: babying 第三人称单数: babies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('constrain', '[kən\'streɪn]', 'vt.强迫；限制', '1. I felt constrained to do what he told me. 做他叫我做的事,我心里很不舒服。 2. She tried to constrain herself from a cough in class. 上课时她竭力忍住不咳嗽。 3. Cold weather constrains the plant\'s growth. 寒冷的天气抑制了植物的生长。 4. Don\'t constrain yourself only to class study. 不要把自己的学习只局限于课堂。', '形容词: constrainable 副词: constrainedly 名词: constrainer 过去式: constrained 过去分词: constrained 现在分词: constraining 第三人称单数: constrains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('annual', '[\'ænjuəl]', 'adj.每年的；年度的；一年生的 n.年刊；一年生植物', '1. The firm has an annual turnover of $75 million. 这家公司的年营业额为7500万美元。 2. Now, again, his annual trip to Paris begins. 现在,他一年一度的巴黎之行又开始了。 3. The kind of plant is a hardy annual. 这种植物是耐寒的一年生植物。 4. Annual or perennial herbs, or tall woody bamboos. 一年生或多年生草本，或高的木质的竹子。 5. His essay is copied from a college annual. 他的论文是从一本大学年刊上抄下来的。', '副词: annually');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('instruction', '[ɪn\'strʌkʃn]', 'n.指令；教学；教诲；说明', '1. The robot follows the instructions given by the computer. 机器人听从计算机给出的指令。 2. Under no circumstances should we neglect the quality of instruction at vocational secondary schools. 任何时候都不要忽略职业中学的教学质量问题。 3. We can derive pleasure, experience, and instruction from good books. 好书能给我们乐趣,经验和教诲。 4. I will take the medicine according to the instructions. 我会按说明来服药的。', '形容词: instructional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hose', '[hoʊz]', 'n.水管；橡皮软管；(复数)长统袜；男士紧身裤 vt.用水管冲洗；<美俚>痛打', '1. On Sundays, he washes his car down with the garden hose. 每逢星期天，他就用花园里的水管把汽车冲洗干净。 2. The stables were sluiced out with water from a hose. 马厩已经用水管子冲洗过了。 3. This fire hose is about sixty feet long. 这段消防水管大约有60 英尺长。 4. He rigged a rubber hose to the tap in the kitchen. 他将一条橡皮软管安装在厨房的水龙头上。 5. Will you hose down my car - it\'s very dirty. 你能用水管冲洗一下我的汽车吗?它太脏了。', '名词复数: hose 过去式: hosed 过去分词: hosed 现在分词: hosing 第三人称单数: hoses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conclusion', '[kən\'kluːʒn]', 'n.结尾；结论；结束', '1. I found the conclusion of her story very exciting. 我觉得她那故事的结尾很激动人心。 2. Some found the conclusion of the film Titanic very disappointing. 有些人觉得电影《泰坦尼克号》的结尾是令人失望的. 3. Your information is inaccurate and your conclusion is therefore wrong. 你的信息不准确，所以你的结论是错误的。 4. So far no correct conclusion has arrived at. 到目前为止,还没有得出任何正确的结论。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fatigue', '[fə\'tiːɡ]', 'n.疲劳；疲乏；劳务杂役 v.（使）疲劳 adj.疲劳的', '1. She hoped to sleep off her fatigue. 她希望睡一觉之后会消除疲劳。 2. The aeroplane wing showed signs of metal fatigue. 机翼显出有金属疲劳的现象。 3. He was beaten out with fatigue when he got home. 他回到家里时已是疲惫不堪。 4. Who is on fatigue duty today? 今天谁担任杂役? 5. The patient fatigues easily. 病人容易疲劳。 6. They were shedding their fatigue. 身上疲劳的感觉渐渐都消失了。', '过去式: fatigued 过去分词: fatigued 现在分词: fatiguing 第三人称单数: fatigues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exploit', '[ɪk\'splɔɪt]', 'vt.剥削；利用；开发；开拓 n.功绩；英勇行为', '1. The capitalists exploit the workers in order to maximize profits. 资本家剥削工人是为了使利润最大化。 2. You must exploit all your spare time to learn English. 你必须利用一切空闲时间来学习英语。 3. People should read the related regulations before they exploit natural resources. 在开发自然资源前，人们应该先了解相关的规定。 4. We should look for blank parts in the market and exploit new market continuously. 我们应找准市场空白,不断开拓新市场。 5. Great men are remembered for their notable exploits. 伟人们因其丰功伟绩而被世人铭记。', '形容词: exploitable 副词: exploitatively 名词: exploitability 过去式: exploited 过去分词: exploited 现在分词: exploiting 第三人称单数: exploits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('linen', '[\'lɪnɪn]', 'n.亚麻布；亚麻线；亚麻制品 adj.亚麻布制的；亚麻的', '1. The old linen smelled of the tomb. 旧亚麻布散发出墓地的气味。 2. Flax is used to make linen. 亚麻用来织亚麻布。 3. Low elasticity, imparting a hard, smooth texture, makes linen subject to wrinkling. 弹性较低，使得质地坚硬光滑，亚麻制品容易起皱纹。 4. He has abandoned suits in favour of linen jackets and khaki trousers and no tie. 他不穿西装，喜欢穿亚麻夹克和卡其布长裤，而且不打领带。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('retrospect', '[\'retrəspekt]', 'n.回顾；追溯 v.回顾；回想；追溯', '1. In retrospect, it\'s easy to see why we were wrong. 回顾过去就很容易明白我们的错处了。 2. In retrospect, that campaign looks like his last hurrah. 回顾起来，那次竞选看起来像是他的最后奋力一博。 3. In retrospect all successful policies seem preordained. 追溯一切成功的政策，看来都有其预兆。 4. In retrospect, it\'s easy to see why we were wrong. 回顾过去就很容易明白我们的错处了。', '名词: retrospection 过去式: retrospected 过去分词: retrospected 现在分词: retrospecting 第三人称单数: retrospects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('week', '[wiːk]', 'n.星期；周', '1. The alterations to your coat will take a week. 你的外衣改一改要花一个星期。 2. The boys have decided to go camping next week. 男孩子们已决定下个星期去露营。 3. I got a new coat in that store last week. 上礼拜我在那家店买了一件新外套。 4. The temperature has stayed hot this week. 本周气温一直都很热。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grandmother', '[\'ɡrænmʌðər]', 'n.(外)祖母', '1. Grandmother used to darn her own stockings. 祖母过去总是自己织补袜子。 2. She helped take care of her aged grandmother. 她帮助照料年迈的祖母。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('govern', '[\'ɡʌvərn]', 'v.统治；支配；管理；规定；控制', '1. Education makes a people easy to lead, but difficult to drive: easy to govern but impossible to slave. 教育让一个民族容易被领导，却很难被驱使；容易被统治，却很难被奴役。 2. You must not be governed by the opinions of others. 你决不要受别人意见的支配。 3. Such laws also govern the chances of commodity production and exchange. 这种规律也支配着商品生产和商品交换的偶然性： 4. Riches either serve or govern the possessor 财富可以侍候主人,也可以支配主人', '形容词: governable 过去式: governed 过去分词: governed 现在分词: governing 第三人称单数: governs 名词: governance');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sacrifice', '[\'sækrɪfaɪs]', 'n.牺牲；祭品；供奉 vt.牺牲；亏本出售；供奉 vi.献祭；(棒球)作牺牲一击', '1. He gave his life as a sacrifice for his country. 他为国牺牲了。 2. She made a big sacrifice for her position today. 她为今天的职位付出了很大的代价。 3. They offered a sacrifice to propitiate the god. 他们供奉祭品以慰诸神。 4. A calf was offered up as a sacrifice to the goddess. 向女神祭献了一头牺牲小牛。 5. You must not sacrifice studies for pleasure. 你不能为享乐而牺牲学业。 6. Sacrifice is the ultimate act of self-giving love. 献祭却是最舍己的爱的行动。', '名词: sacrificer 过去式: sacrificed 过去分词: sacrificed 现在分词: sacrificing 第三人称单数: sacrifices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coin', '[kɔɪn]', 'n.硬币；金钱 vt.铸造（钱币）；创造（新词） adj.硬币的；投币的', '1. He put a coin into the insertion slot. 他往投币孔投入一枚硬币。 2. He paid me in coin. 他付给我的都是硬币。 3. Father dug up an old coin in the garden. 父亲在花园里掘出一枚古钱币。 4. They were granted the right to coin money. 他们获得铸造钱币的授权。 5. The reverse of the coin was stamped with an eagle. 硬币的反面压印的是一只鹰。', '形容词: coinable 名词: coiner 过去式: coined 过去分词: coined 现在分词: coining 第三人称单数: coins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('paper', '[\'peɪpər]', 'n.纸；文件；报纸；论文；票据；壁纸 v.用纸包；用纸糊；贴壁纸 adj.纸制的；似纸的；有名无实的', '1. That paper has yellowed with age. 那张纸因年代久远而泛黄了。 2. The letter was written on a single sheet of paper. 这封信只用一张纸写成。 3. He refused to subscribe his name to the paper. 他拒绝在这文件上签字。 4. The paper advertises for two editors. 这家报纸招聘两名编辑。 5. I need a paper box. 我需要一个纸盒子。', '名词: paperer 过去式: papered 过去分词: papered 现在分词: papering 第三人称单数: papers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stain', '[steɪn]', 'n.污点；瑕疵；着色剂；染料 v.弄脏；玷污；着色', '1. The stain on his shirt is difficult to clean off. 他衬衣上的污点很难去除掉。 2. It will remain an indelible stain on his memory. 这将成为他记忆中一个不可磨灭的污点。 3. Such a man is a stain to humanity. 这种人是人类的耻辱。 4. There isn\'t a stain on her reputation. 她的名誉没有半点瑕疵。 5. These carpets won\'t stain easily. 这些地毯不易弄脏。', '形容词: stainable 名词: stainer 过去式: stained 过去分词: stained 现在分词: staining 第三人称单数: stains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rely', '[rɪ\'laɪ]', 'vi.依靠；信任', '1. They have to rely on the river for their water. 他们用水只好依靠这条河。 2. A man should rely upon his own power. 人类应该依靠自身的力量。 3. You can\'t rely on his assistance. 你不能指望他能帮助你。 4. We are relying on your decision. 我们相信你的判断。', '名词: relier 过去式: relied 过去分词: relied 现在分词: relying 第三人称单数: relies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('audio', '[\'ɔːdioʊ]', 'adj.声音的；成音频率的 n.音频；音响设备', '1. The reproductive quality of audio tapes has improved enormously. 录音磁带的复制质量有了很大改进。 2. Voice commands could not set the audio device. 声音命令无法设置音频设备。 3. Music, of course, is just a special case of general audio, but an important one. 当然，音乐是声波的一种特殊情况，但却是重要的一种。 4. In audio, a very low frequency oscillation often resulting from a positive feedback path in an amplifier system. 在音响设备中出现的振荡频率极低的低频振荡，常因放大系统的正反馈回路引起。', '名词复数: audios');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fiber', '[\'faɪbə]', 'n.纤维(物质)；性格；质地', '1. It was not until 1884 that the first artificial fiber was made. 直到一八八四年，第一个人造纤维才制造出来。 2. Scientists are recommending that people eat more fiber. 科学家建议人们多吃些纤维素。 3. He is a man of real fiber. 他是一个有骨气的男子。 4. I love my country with every fiber of my being. 我深爱我的祖国。', '形容词: fibered');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anger', '[\'æŋɡər]', 'n.愤怒；怒火 vt.激怒 vi.发火', '1. His charges were met with cries of anger. 他的指控遭到一阵愤怒的反对声。 2. His face was inflamed with anger. 他的脸因愤怒而涨得通红。 3. He was inflamed with anger. 他满腔怒火。 4. She felt anger rise in her heart. 她感到心中冒起怒火。 5. The eagle is eager to anger the tiger in danger. 鹰渴望激怒处在危险中的老虎。 6. He was roused to anger by the insult. 他因受辱而生气。', '过去式: angered 过去分词: angered 现在分词: angering 第三人称单数: angers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pneumonia', '[nuː\'moʊniə]', 'n.肺炎', '1. His disease was complicated by pneumonia. 他的病因肺炎并发症而变得更严重。 2. Pneumonia carried him off last winter. 他去年患肺炎逝世了。 3. Set up by a severe cold in October, Mary could not throw off her pneumonia. 玛丽十月间得过一场重感冒，抵抗力大为减弱，因而肺炎难以痊愈。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('debt', '[det]', 'n.债务；恩情；负债状态；义务；罪', '1. He promised to pay his debt within a month. 他保证在1个月内偿还债务。 2. If I pay all my debts I\'ll have no money. 我若还请所有欠债就分文不剩了。 3. We owe you a debt of gratitude for you help. 承蒙帮助，感恩不尽。 4. The company is deep in debt. 这家公司正负债累累。', '形容词: debtless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cloth', '[klɔːθ]', 'n.布；布料；一块布', '1. This piece of cloth was eaten by a moth. 这块布被蠹虫蛀坏了。 2. Cloth is sold by the yard. 布是按码卖的。 3. This piece of cloth has bad coloration. 这块布料染的不好。 4. I rubbed the window with a cloth. 我用一块布擦窗子。', '名词复数: cloths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cinema', '[\'sɪnəmə]', 'n.电影院；电影(艺术；拍摄；技术)', '1. They streamed out of the cinema. 他们涌出电影院。 2. There is a telephone booth near the cinema. 电影院附近有一个电话亭。 3. He has an urge to become a cinema star. 他渴望当一名电影明星。 4. When going to the cinema we prefer Czech films and the country has a great tradition for film-making. 去电影院时，我们更偏爱捷克电影，这个国家有了不起的电影拍摄传统。', '形容词: cinematic 副词: cinematically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('container', '[kən\'teɪnər]', 'n.容器；集装箱', '1. A reactor is a container for chemical reaction. 反应器是进行化学反应的容器。 2. The volume of this container is 2 cubic meters. 这个容器的容量是两立方米。 3. The goods are packed in airtight container. 货物被装在密封的集装箱内。 4. You need to empty the container. 你必须腾空这个集装箱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discourse', '[\'dɪskɔːrs]', 'n.谈话，讨论；（一系列的）演讲，文章 vi.讲述；谈话 vt.叙述；讨论', '1. The judges had solemn discourse together. 法官们在一起严肃地交谈。 2. They listened to his discourse on human relations. 他们听他作关于人际关系的演讲。 3. He discoursed impressively on Newton\'s theory of gravity. 他讲述了牛顿的引力定律，给人以深刻的印象。 4. The teacher is discoursing with him. 老师正在和他谈话。 5. The old man discoursed his experiences when he was a child. 这位老人叙述了他孩子时的经历。', '名词: discourser 过去式: discoursed 过去分词: discoursed 现在分词: discoursing 第三人称单数: discourses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hammer', '[\'hæmər]', 'n.锤；榔头 vi.锤击；反复敲打 vt.锤打；严厉批评', '1. He hit the nail into the wall with a hammer. 他用一把锤子把钉子打进墙里去。 2. He smashed a hole in the window with a hammer. 他用锤子在玻璃上打了个洞。 3. He took a hammer and recessed a hole into the wall. 他拿起一个榔头，在墙上敲出一个洞。 4. He dashed into the porch and began to hammer on the door. 他冲上门廊用力捶起门来。 5. The police hammered the door. 警察不停地敲门。', '名词: hammerer 过去式: hammered 过去分词: hammered 现在分词: hammering 第三人称单数: hammers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gratitude', '[\'ɡrætɪtuːd]', 'n.感激；感谢；感恩', '1. His heart overflowed with gratitude. 他的心里充满了感激之情。 2. She showed me her gratitude by inviting me to dinner. 她邀请我吃饭以表示她的感激。 3. We welcome the opportunity to express our gratitude. 我们能有机会表示谢意十分高兴。 4. We owe you a debt of gratitude for you help. 承蒙帮助，感恩不尽。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arrow', '[\'æroʊ]', 'n.箭；箭头', '1. The arrow just split the apple in half. 箭把苹果分成两半。 2. The arrow flew straight and true to its mark. 那箭不偏不斜地直朝目标飞去。 3. The bow twanged and the arrow whistled through the air. 那张弓发出“崩”的一声,箭随之呼啸而去。 4. The arrow indicates where we are. 箭头表示我们现在所在之处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inspect', '[ɪn\'spekt]', 'v.检查；视察', '1. Police were called out to keep at the airport, and inspect the arriving planes. 警察们被紧急召集起来去守卫机场，并对到达的飞机进行检查。 2. It was strange that nobody inspected my ticket before I got on the train. 很奇怪，我上火车前，竟然没有人查看我的车票。 3. Customs officers inspect our baggage. 海关人员检查我们的行李。 4. The government sent him to inspect our school. 政府派他来视察我们学校。', '形容词: inspective 过去式: inspected 过去分词: inspected 现在分词: inspecting 第三人称单数: inspects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stalk', '[stɔːk]', 'n.茎；梗 n.跟踪；高视阔步 v.悄悄靠近；跟踪；蔓延；高视阔步地走', '1. It doesn\' t produce a stalk at all the first year? 在头一年绝对长不出茎秆? 2. He cut off the flowers at the stalk with a pair of scissors. 他用剪子连花带茎都剪下来。 3. He ate the apple, stalk and all. 他把那个苹果吃了个干净，连梗都没剩下。 4. He moved like a tiger stalking its prey. 他像老虎一样悄悄潜近他的猎物。', '形容词: stalky 名词: stalker 过去式: stalked 过去分词: stalked 现在分词: stalking 第三人称单数: stalks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weekly', '[\'wiːkli]', 'adj.每周的；一周一次的；周刊的 n.周刊；周报 adv.每周；一周一次', '1. We should work out what our weekly costs are. 我们应该算出我们每周的花费。 2. The child has a weekly allowance of five dollars. 这孩子每星期有五元零用钱。 3. I\'ll have to discontinue these weekly visits. 我每周一次的访问得停止了。 4. Shall we assign Thursdays for our weekly meetings? 我们把每周例会定在星期四好吗? 5. There is an interesting article in this weekly. 这期的周刊上有一篇有趣的文章。 6. We played chess two or three times weekly. 我们每周下两三次棋。', '名词复数: weeklies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resist', '[rɪ\'zɪst]', 'v.抵制；抵抗；反抗；忍住 n.防蚀涂层', '1. Many young people could not resist the spiritual pollution. 很多年轻人不能抵制精神污染。 2. They are determined to resist invasion. 他们决定抵抗入侵。 3. The nobility usually resist social changes. 贵族通常反对社会变革。 4. They were powerless to resist. 他们无力反抗。', '名词: resister 过去式: resisted 过去分词: resisted 现在分词: resisting 第三人称单数: resists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beauty', '[\'bjuːti]', 'n.美人；美丽；美的东西', '1. Beauty\'s tears are lovelier than her smile. 美人的泪水比微笑更可爱。 2. His wife is an unmatched beauty. 他妻子是一个倾国倾城的美人。 3. Words cannot describe the beauty of the scene. 语言难以描述那景色之美丽。 4. The beauty of the scene filled us with enchantment. 我们被美丽的景色迷住了。', '名词复数: beauties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tape', '[teɪp]', 'n.磁带；胶布；终点 v.录音；录像；用胶布粘；用绳子捆绑；用卷尺测量', '1. I\'ve got all the Beethoven symphonies on tape. 我有贝多芬交响乐全部的录音带。 2. Cassette tape recorders are gradually out of date now. 现在,盒式磁带录音机渐渐过时了。 3. You\'d better put some insulating tape on electric wires. 你最好给电线裹上绝缘胶布。 4. The two runners broke the tape together. 两位赛跑运动员在终点同时撞线。 5. I taped a late-night radio show and listened to it in the morning. 我录下午夜的收音机节目,早上听。', '形容词: tapeable 过去式: taped 过去分词: taped 现在分词: taping 第三人称单数: tapes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recipient', '[rɪ\'sɪpiənt]', 'n.接受者；收信人', '1. China is now the world\'s sixth-largest trading partner and the second-largest recipient of foreign investment after the United States. 中国现在是世界第6大贸易国，仅次于美国的世界第二大外国投资接受国。 2. The recipients of prizes had their names printed in the paper. 获奖者名单登在报上。 3. The postman spent almost a whole day looking for the recipient of the letter. 邮递员几乎花了整整一天时间寻找该信的收信人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rectangle', '[\'rektæŋɡl]', 'n.长方形；矩形', '1. Rectangle is coming into fashion. 长方形开始流行了。 2. He folded his newspaper into a neat rectangle. 他将报纸折成一个整整齐齐的长方形。 3. A rectangle has four right angles. 一个矩形有四个直角。 4. He drew a rectangle on the blackboard. 他在黑板上画了个矩形。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('patrol', '[pə\'troʊl]', 'n.巡逻；巡查 v.巡逻；巡查', '1. Terrorists attacked two soldiers on patrol. 恐怖分子袭击了两名正在巡逻的士兵。 2. The patrol was waylaid by bandits. 巡逻队遭到土匪伏击。 3. The police hustled the tramps into the patrol car. 警察将那些流浪者强行推入巡逻车中。 4. The plane will patrol Australia\'s coastline. 未来这架飞机的任务是巡逻澳洲海岸线。', '名词: patroller 过去式: patrolled 过去分词: patrolled 现在分词: patrolling 第三人称单数: patrols');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weigh', '[weɪ]', 'v.衡量；称(重量)；重达 ...', '1. He weighed the ideas in his mind. 他在脑中权衡着这些想法。 2. It\'s been weighing on my mind for days whether to tell her or not. 我这几天心烦意乱，不知道应该不应告诉她。 3. The branches of the trees were weighed down by snow. 树枝被雪压弯了。 4. He weighed in at several pounds below the limit. 他赛前量体重比规定限度少几磅。', '名词: weigher 过去式: weighed 过去分词: weighed 现在分词: weighing 第三人称单数: weighs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('county', '[\'kaʊnti]', 'n.郡；县 adj.有郡中豪绅习气的', '1. Her jocund character made her the most popular girl in the county. 她快乐的个性使她成为这个郡最受欢迎的女孩。 2. He was elected sheriff of the county. 他被选为县警长。 3. The soil in that county is very poor. 那个县的土壤十分贫瘠。 4. He belongs to the county set. 他属于郡中豪绅阶层。', '名词复数: counties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hell', '[hel]', 'n.地狱；阴间；苦境；极大的痛苦 n.究竟（用以加强语气） int.该死(用以表示愤怒或惊讶)', '1. The preacher warned us about punishments in hell. 传道士用地狱里的惩罚来告诫我们。 2. The priest said they would go to hell for their sins. 牧师说，他们将因罪恶而下地狱。 3. Hades is the Greek word for Hell. 阴间是地狱的希腊语。 4. Her house is the way to hell, going down to the chambers of death. 她的家是通往阴间的路，是下到死亡的宫房。 5. What the hell do you think you are doing? 你认为你究竟在干什么? 6. Hell! What a mass! Are they masochism? 该死！这么多！他们是受虐狂么?', '过去式: helled 过去分词: helled 现在分词: helling 第三人称单数: hells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('integrity', '[ɪn\'teɡrəti]', 'n.完整；完善；正直；诚实', '1. We must respect each other\'s territorial integrity. 我们应当尊重彼此的领土完整。 2. We all have an interest in maintaining the integrity of the ecosystem. 维持生态系统的完整是我们共同的利益。 3. One of the most important features of the steel cables is their structural integrity. 钢索最重要的特点之一，是结构的完善性。 4. My husband is a man of the highest integrity. 我丈夫是个非常正直的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('last', '[læst]', 'v.持续；维持 adj.最近的；上一个的；末尾的；最后的 adv.最后；最近一次 n.最后来的人（或发生的事）；鞋楦(做鞋的模型)', '1. The hot weather lasted until September. 炎热的天气持续到九月。 2. The wind is changing round, so the storm won\'t last long. 风正在转向,因此暴风雨不会持续太长的时间。 3. Economically, one tin of oil will last at least three months. 如果节省地用的,这罐油就会维持至少三个月。 4. I thought her last book was one of her best. 我认为她最近出版的那本书是她的最佳著作之一。 5. He came last in the race. 他赛跑落得了最后。', '副词: lastly 过去式: lasted 过去分词: lasted 现在分词: lasting 第三人称单数: lasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grey', '[ɡreɪ]', 'adj.灰色的 n.灰色 vi.变成灰色 =<美>gray', '1. Have you any grey pullovers in stock? 你们有灰色套头毛衣的现货吗？ 2. Today, the canopy of the heavens is grey. 今天的天幕是灰色的。 3. The most popular color this autumn is grey. 今年最流行灰色。 4. The ashes from burnt grass make a good grey. 草灰可以成为很好的灰色染料。 5. Wood turns grey if weathered for a long time. 木材如果风干时间较长就变成灰色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('monster', '[\'mɑːnstər]', 'n.怪物；恶人；巨物 adj.巨大的；庞大的', '1. A hideous monster attacked the helpless villagers. 有个丑恶的怪物袭击了手无寸铁的村民。 2. I saw a horrible monster in the forest. 我在林中见到一头可怕的怪物。 3. The judge told the murderer that he was a monster. 法官对凶手说他是一个穷凶极恶的人。 4. He\'s a lovely man, but when he gets jealous he turns into a monster. 他是个讨人喜欢的人,但是当他嫉妒起来时,就成了一个恶魔。 5. Many monster high-rise buildings spring up all over the city. 许多巨大的高层建筑在这座城市拔地而起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relieve', '[rɪ\'liːv]', 'v.救济；减轻；解除；偷', '1. The Government acted quickly to relieve the widespread distress caused by the earthquake. 地震造成大范围的灾难,政府迅速采取行动赈济灾民。 2. This medicine will relieve your headache. 这药将减轻你的头痛。 3. The route was designed to relieve traffic congestion. 这条路是为缓解交通拥挤而开辟的。 4. The general was relieved of his command. 将军被解除了指挥权。', '形容词: relievable 名词: reliever 过去式: relieved 过去分词: relieved 现在分词: relieving 第三人称单数: relieves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clothe', '[kloʊð]', 'vt.穿上；赋予', '1. He had to work hard to feed and clothe the large family. 他必须努力工作才能使全家有饭吃，有衣穿。 2. They clothe their children in the latest fashions. 他们给他们的孩子穿最时髦的服装。 3. We clothe our thoughts in words. 我们用语言表达思想。', '过去式: clothed/clad 过去分词: clothed/clad 现在分词: clothing 第三人称单数: clothes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('questionnaire', '[ˌkwestʃə\'ner]', 'n.调查表；问卷', '1. We gave them some questionnaires for collecting data. 为了收集数据我们发给他们一些调查表。 2. Please fill up the blanks in the questionnaire. 请把调查表填写一下。 3. Please complete and return the enclosed questionnaire. 所附问卷请填妥交回。 4. Is a questionnaire answered by 500 people truly representative of national opinion? 一份调查问卷有500人作答,是否能真正代表全国人民的意见?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('special', '[\'speʃl]', 'adj.特别的；特殊的；专门的 n.特别的东西；特刊；特色菜；特价', '1. She is a special friend of mine. 她是我一个特别的朋友。 2. We have a special offer for our regular patrons. 我们给予老顾客特别的优惠。 3. If needed, give us your special requirements. 如果需要,告诉我们您的特殊要求。 4. This is a special case, deserving special treatment. 这是个特殊的案件，应该获得特殊处理。 5. There are lots of TV Christmas specials for children this year. 今年又很多针对儿童的特别的电视圣诞节目。', '副词: specially 名词: specialness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('focus', '[\'foʊkəs]', 'n.焦点；焦距；中心 v.（使）集中；聚集', '1. He always wants to be the focus of attention. 他总想成为注意力的焦点。 2. He took out the binoculars and adjusted the focus. 他取出双筒望远镜并调整了焦距。 3. The main focus of this manual is the management of fresh ground water resources. 本指南的主要中心是地下淡水资源的管理。 4. The noise made it hard for me to focus on work. 噪音让我无法集中注意力工作。', '名词: focuser 名词复数: focuses 过去式: focused/focussed 过去分词: focused/focussed 现在分词: focusing/focussing 第三人称单数: focuses/focusses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tactic', '[\'tæktɪk]', 'n.战略；策略', '1. The new tactic was put into operation early in 1939. 这个新的战略是在1939年初开始运用的。 2. The team won the game thanks to Jeff\'s fabulous spot tactic. 多亏了杰夫当场制定的英明战略，他的球队赢了。 3. Reducing prices is a common sales tactic. 降价是常用的销售策略。 4. Confrontation is not always the best tactic. 对抗并非总是上策。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('moss', '[mɔːs]', 'n.苔藓；泥沼 vt.使长满苔藓', '1. He is found asleep on a pillow of leaves and moss. 有人看见他枕着树叶和苔藓睡着了。 2. Moss affects the northern slopes. 朝北的山坡易生苔。 3. A rolling stone gathers no moss. 滚石不生苔。', '过去式: mossed 过去分词: mossed 现在分词: mossing 第三人称单数: mosses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('off', '[ɔːf]', 'adv.表示状态的关闭或离开 prep.离开；在 ... 之外 adj.空闲的；离开的；关闭的 v.离开；脱下', '1. The singer was led off the stage by the maestro. 歌唱家由那位著名的指挥领着离开了舞台。 2. Off campus, they faced hostility. 在校园之外，他们遭人敌意。 3. The plane took off and ascended steadily until it was out of sight. 飞机起飞之后平稳地逐渐升空直到消失在视野之外。 4. He forgot to turn off the gas torch when he left. 他离开的时候忘记关掉气焊焊炬了。 5. Boring! We should just off him and be done with it! 无聊!我们应该干掉他,这样一切就搞掂了。', '过去式: offed 过去分词: offed 现在分词: offing 第三人称单数: offs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impact', '[\'ɪmpækt]', 'n.影响；冲击力；撞击 vt.挤入；压紧；撞击；对 ... 发生影响 vi.冲击；撞击；产生影响', '1. Seasonality or economic cycles will have minimal impact on secular trends. 季节性或经济周期两者对长期趋势的影响都不大。 2. But what these people fail to see is that international tourism may bring about a disastrous impact on our environment and local history. 但是这些人忽视了国际旅游可能会给当地环境和历史造成的灾难性的影响。 3. The impact of the crash hurtled the driver against the windshield of the car. 碰撞的震力使驾驶员猛撞于车子的挡风玻璃上。 4. The impact of the stone against the windowpane shattered the glass. 石头撞击窗户打碎了玻璃。 5. A vast crowd impacted the square. 广场上挤集了一大群人。 6. The company\'s performance was impacted by the high value of the pound. 公司的业绩受到了英镑高值的冲击。', '名词: impaction 过去式: impacted 过去分词: impacted 现在分词: impacting 第三人称单数: impacts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bore', '[bɔːr]', 'v.使厌烦；开凿；钻孔；挖掘；盯着看 n.讨厌的人；麻烦事；(管道、枪炮等的)孔；涌潮；(找水或石油的)钻孔 动词bear的过去式.', '1. He bored us all by talking for hours about his new house. 他连续几个小时大谈他的新房子，使我们大家都厌烦透了。 2. They are going to bore a tunnel through this mountain. 他们打算开凿一条穿越此山的隧道。 3. This drill can bore through rock. 这台钻机能钻透岩石。 4. Worms have bored into the wood. 虫子已经蛀穿了木料。 5. He was making a bore of himself. 他快要使自己变成一个惹人讨厌的人物了。', '过去式: bored 过去分词: bored 现在分词: boring 第三人称单数: bores');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('turbine', '[\'tɜːrbaɪn]', 'n.涡轮', '1. The turbine is spun by the high-pressure gases. 涡轮由高压燃气驱动旋转。 2. Check no damage for fan blades and turbine blades. 检查风扇叶片和涡轮叶片无损坏迹象。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('make', '[meɪk]', 'v.做；制造；使得；赚（钱）；成功；达成 n.性格；式样；制造；生产量', '1. If I had the time, I \'d make something better. 如果有时间的话,我会做些更好吃的东西。 2. In the old China, we can\'t even make a nail, let alone machines. 在旧中国,我们连一个钉子都造不了,更不用说制造机器了。 3. Her jokes made us all laugh. 她说的笑话把我们都逗乐了。 4. If you take my advice, you will make a lot of money. 如果你采纳我的建议,你将赚很多钱。 5. Finally,I\'ve got to find out what make of man he was. 最后,我终于知道了他是怎么样的一个人。', '形容词: makable 过去式: made 过去分词: made 现在分词: making 第三人称单数: makes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spade', '[speɪd]', 'n.铲子；铁锹 n.黑桃 v.铲', '1. She got a spade and laid to with the others. 她拿了把铲子和大家一起大干起来。 2. My father used a special spade for digging turf. 我父亲用一把特别的铲子挖草皮。 3. He was digging potatoes with a spade. 他正在用铁锹挖马铃薯。 4. It\'s hard to work this soil with such an old spade. 用这样一把旧铁锹挖地真费劲。 5. My partner surprised me by leading with a spade. 我的搭档先出黑桃，使我感到吃惊。 6. Orders came that we should spade the trench in an hour. 有命令要我们必须在一小时内挖好战壕。', '名词: spader 过去式: spaded 过去分词: spaded 现在分词: spading 第三人称单数: spades');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('restrain', '[rɪ\'streɪn]', 'vt.抑制；阻止；束缚；剥夺', '1. He couldn\'t restrain his curiosity. 他抑制不住自己的好奇心。 2. She tried to restrain her sobs. 她设法抑制住自己的悲泣。 3. Shame may restrain what the law does not prohibit. 羞耻或许能阻止法律所不能禁止之事。 4. We must not restrain children of their liberty. 我们绝对不要限制孩子们的自由。', '形容词: restrainable 副词: restrainedly 名词: restrainer 过去式: restrained 过去分词: restrained 现在分词: restraining 第三人称单数: restrains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('minority', '[maɪ\'nɔːrəti]', 'n.少数；少数民族；未成年', '1. Only a minority of British households do not have a car. 英国只有少数家庭没有汽车。 2. A small minority voted against the motion. 投票反对该提议的人占少数。 3. The question of which state the minority group should belong to was decided by (a) plebiscite. 该少数民族应归属哪一州的问题已由公民投票表决。 4. There are 56 minorities in our country. 我国有56个少数民族。', '名词复数: minorities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assimilate', '[ə\'sɪməleɪt]', 'v.使同化；吸收', '1. The USA has assimilated people from many different countries. 美国已经同化了许多来自不同国家的人。 2. Europeans and Jews do not readily assimilate. 欧洲人和犹太人不易同化。 3. Immigrants often want to assimilate quickly. 移民经常想迅速同化。 4. Some foods are assimilated more easily than others. 有些食物比另一些食物容易吸收。', '名词: assimilator 过去式: assimilated 过去分词: assimilated 现在分词: assimilating 第三人称单数: assimilates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appear', '[ə\'pɪr]', 'vi.出现；出版；显得；好像；登场', '1. A ship appeared on the horizon. 船出现在水平线上。 2. His book appears on the market. 他的书出版了。 3. An article about him appeared in the paper. 一篇有关他的文章在报上发表。 4. She appeared very confident. 她显得很自信。', '过去式: appeared 过去分词: appeared 现在分词: appearing 第三人称单数: appears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peasant', '[\'peznt]', 'n.农民', '1. That night we put up in a peasant\'s home. 那天晚上我们住在一个农民的家里。 2. It is the lament of an impoverished peasant. 它是一个已贫穷化的农民的哀词。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mountain', '[\'maʊntən]', 'n.大量；山；山脉；高山', '1. I have a mountain of work to do. 我有一大堆工作要做。 2. The mountain is 3500 meters high. 这座山有3500米高。 3. The mountain tops are covered with snow. 白雪覆盖着山顶。 4. This mountain runs from east to west. 这是一座东西走向的山脉。', '形容词: mountainy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('client', '[\'klaɪənt]', 'n.委托人；客户', '1. If a lawyer has plenty of clients, he grows rich. 律师如果有大量的诉讼委托人，就会财源不断。 2. The lawyer explained the legal technicalities to his client. 律师给委托人解释法律上的要点。 3. Counsel for the defence submitted that his client was clearly innocent. 被告的律师辩称其委托人显然是无辜的。 4. Now you can build the response to the client. 现在,您可以构建对客户端的响应。', '形容词: cliental 名词: clientage');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('costly', '[\'kɔːstli]', 'adj.昂贵的；代价高的', '1. The costly post was postponed because of the frost. 那件昂贵的邮件由于霜的缘故而延搁。 2. Lighting a surface can be a costly operation. 光照一个表面可以是一个昂贵的操作。', '比较级: costlier 最高级: costliest 名词: costliness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ridge', '[rɪdʒ]', 'n.脊；山脊；山脉；隆起部 v.（使）成山脊', '1. Recurvature follows after it traverses the ridge axis. 预料尼伯特将于横过副高脊线后开始转向。 2. Riding on the ridge of the bridge, the proud bride shouts loudly to the cloud. 骄傲的新娘骑在桥脊上对着云大声喊。 3. He walked along the mountain ridge. 他顺着山脊走。 4. The evening before the battle, Wellington took up a defensive position along, and to the rear of, a long ridge. 那场战斗的前夜，威灵顿沿一条长长的山脊背后占据了一个防守阵地。 5. The floor of the Atlantic ridges in the middle from north to south. 大西洋洋底在中部形成由北向南的海脊。', '过去式: ridged 过去分词: ridged 现在分词: ridging 第三人称单数: ridges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('convict', '[kən\'vɪkt]', 'vt.宣判 ... 有罪；使 ... 知罪 n.囚犯；罪犯 adj.被定罪的', '1. You can\'t convict a man of a crime on circumstantial evidence alone. 不能只靠旁证就判定一个人有罪。 2. The criminal was convicted of murder. 歹徒被判谋杀罪。 3. He was convicted of his errors. 他认识到自己所犯的过失。 4. The convict fled away with a hostage. 囚犯带着一个人质跑了。 5. Let a convict person go free without any punishment. 让被定罪的人自由，不进行任何惩罚。', '过去式: convicted 过去分词: convicted 现在分词: convicting 第三人称单数: convicts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bloody', '[\'blʌdi]', 'adj.流血的；血腥的；嗜杀的 vt.使流血 adv.[俚]非常', '1. And the fingers trying to staunch the bloody wound at his neck. 和试图止住脖子上正在流血的伤口的手指时会有什么感觉。 2. It eventually came home to the people that the war would be long and bloody. 人们终于认识到，这场战争将是持久的和流血的。 3. Some people like to watch the bloody films. 有些人喜欢看血腥的影片。 4. In Warsaw there is bloody street fighting. 华沙市内发生了血腥的巷战。 5. She did bloody well to win that race. 她非常出色地赢得了那场赛跑。', '副词: bloodily 比较级: bloodier 最高级: bloodiest 名词: bloodiness 过去式: bloodied 过去分词: bloodied 现在分词: bloodying 第三人称单数: bloodies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('turbulent', '[\'tɜːrbjələnt]', 'adj.狂暴的；骚动的；动荡的；汹涌的', '1. He was born in that turbulent period of history. 他出生在那个动荡的历史时期。 2. In the turbulent war age, he guides the elf to know the death aright. 在动荡的战争年代，他导引精灵们正确认识死亡。 3. The oarsman was feathering through the turbulent waves. 划桨者正平掠过汹涌的波浪。 4. The Rhosili is a turbulent, swift-flowing river, full of dangerous rapids and currents. 罗西里是一条汹涌的迅速滚滚的河，充满着危险的险滩和湍流。', '副词: turbulently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('friend', '[frend]', 'n.朋友；支持者；友人 vt.与 ... 为友', '1. A friend in need is a friend indeed. 患难之交才是真朋友。 2. My friend invited me to dine out. 我的朋友邀请我出去吃饭。 3. I made friends with Bill in high school. 我和比尔在高中就成为朋友。 4. Mr. Green has been a friend of community charity. 格林先生一直是社区慈善事业的支持者。 5. A joke never gains an enemy but loses a friend. 戏谑不能化敌为友，只能使人失去朋友。', '形容词: friendless 名词: friendlessness 过去式: friended 过去分词: friended 现在分词: friending 第三人称单数: friends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('path', '[pæθ]', 'n.路线；小路；小径；轨道；路程', '1. A bullet describes a curved path in the air. 子弹在空中作曲线运动。 2. We bumped up and down along the gravel path. 我们沿砾石小路颠簸而行。 3. They went out for a walk on the gravelled path. 他们在碎石小径上散步。 4. I very much hope that this is merely a temporary phenomenon before a path could be found for emerging Asia to move again towards and adhere to financial freedom. 我衷心希望这只属暂时的现象,不久亚洲新兴市场便会重回开放金融的轨道。', '名词复数: paths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('help', '[help]', 'v.帮助；有助于；促进；擅自拿取；（不）能防止或避免某事物 n.帮助；援助；帮手；佣人；仆人 int.救命！', '1. Your advice helped me a lot. 你的意见对我大有帮助。 2. I\'ll do everything possible to help you. 我会尽一切可能帮助你。 3. Trade helps industry to develop. 贸易促进工业发展。 4. This latest development doesn\'t exactly help. 这一最新情况对事情并没有真正好处。 5. Thank you for your kind help. 谢谢你好意相助。 6. Aaah, the monster\'s coming. Run! Help! 啊，怪物出来了，快跑啊！救命啊！', '过去式: helped 过去分词: helped 现在分词: helping 第三人称单数: helps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fundamental', '[ˌfʌndə\'mentl]', 'adj.基本的；根本的；重要的 n.基础；基本原理', '1. For something fundamental has changed in Venezuela. 因为在委内瑞拉，有一些基本的东西已经改变了。 2. Trial by the jury is a fundamental right. 有陪审团陪同审判是一项基本的权利。 3. From the outset, it had two fundamental flaws. 从一开始，这一合作就有两个根本的缺陷。 4. The fundamental ones are embodied in the Party Constitution. 党章是最根本的党规党法。 5. Primary is about fundamental play. 原始与基础游戏有关。', '副词: fundamentally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('smoke', '[smoʊk]', 'n.烟；抽烟；无常的事物 v.吸烟；以烟熏；冒烟', '1. The stove let out a puff of smoke. 炉子里冒出一股烟。 2. The smoke from chimney is spreading out in the sky. 烟囱冒出的烟正在空中散开。 3. The smoke of the burning house could be seen many blocks away. 着火的房子的冒出的烟在几个街区外都能看到。 4. They stopped work to have a smoke. 他们停下工作吸口烟。 5. It\'s against the rules of the school to smoke. 吸烟是违反校规的。', '形容词: smokable 过去式: smoked 过去分词: smoked 现在分词: smoking 第三人称单数: smokes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('significant', '[sɪɡ\'nɪfɪkənt]', 'adj.重要的；有意义的；意味深长的；显著的', '1. The question under discussion is significant. 讨论中的问题是重要的。 2. Economic conditions are significant in many ways. 经济条件在许多方面都是很重要的。 3. All of us want our lives to be significant. 我们每个人都希望我们的人生是有意义的。 4. It was truly a significant conversation. 这是非常有意义的谈话。', '副词: significantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ready', '[\'redi]', 'adj.准备好的；现成的；乐意的；情愿的', '1. The troops were ready for anything. 部队已做好了一切准备。 2. The letter is ready for the post. 信已准备好，可以寄出了。 3. I have no ready answer to the question. 我没有现成的答案。 4. We are ready to render them assistance. 我们乐意援助他们。', '比较级: readier 最高级: readiest 名词: readiness 过去式: readied 过去分词: readied 现在分词: readying 第三人称单数: readies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('picture', '[\'pɪktʃər]', 'n.照片；影片；描述；图画 vt.想像；画；拍照', '1. May I take a picture of you? 我可以给你照相吗？ 2. The Pianist is the fourth movie nominated for Best Picture. 《钢琴家》是第4部获得最佳影片提名的电影。 3. The book gives a good picture of everyday life in ancient rome. 那部书对古罗马人的日常生活描写得很生动。 4. This book gives a good picture of life in China 100 hundred years ago. 这本书形象地描写了一百年前的中国生活。 5. I can\'t picture the village without the old church. 我无法设想村子里没有那座旧教堂像什麽样子', '过去式: pictured 过去分词: pictured 现在分词: picturing 第三人称单数: pictures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('integral', '[\'ɪntɪɡrəl]', 'adj.完整的；构成整体所必需的 n.[数] 积分；完整', '1. The transit line is an integral transportation link for the 2010 Winter Olympics. 该隧道是温哥华为2010年冬季奥运会打造的一条完整地下线路。 2. The kitchen is an integral part of a house. 厨房是房子不可缺的部分 3. These policies form an integral whole. 这是很完整的。 4. The bodies of the carts were integral, that is made of one moulding. 马车的车身是完整的，而且是根据同一个模型做出来的。', '副词: integrally 名词: integrality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('amplify', '[\'æmplɪfaɪ]', 'v.扩大；详述；增强', '1. We must amplify our effort by working a lot harder. 我们必须更努力地工作来扩大成果。 2. The new manager wants to amplify the company. 新经理想要扩大公司。 3. A manufacturer can amplify the demand of a product by advertising widely. 厂商能用大做广告的方法来扩大人们对产品的需求。 4. Please amplify your remarks by giving us some examples. 请举例详述你的话。', '过去式: amplified 过去分词: amplified 现在分词: amplifying 第三人称单数: amplifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('catalog', '[\'kætəlɔːg]', 'n.目录；大学概况手册；商品型录 vt.做目录；分类说明；名入列表 vi.(商品)在型录中明码标价', '1. You can look for the book in the library catalog. 你可以在图书馆的图书目录上查找这本书。 2. These names are to be listed in the catalog. 这些名字将列入目录。 3. Please show me a catalog of your books. 请拿一本图书目录给我看看。 4. Has the Harvard catalog come yet? 哈佛大学简介来了吗？ 5. Can you catalog all these books? 你能给所有这些书编目录吗？ 6. This stamp catalogues at two dollars. 这张邮票的目录价格为2美元。', '异体字: catalogue 名词: cataloger 过去式: cataloged/catalogued 过去分词: cataloged/catalogued 现在分词: cataloging/cataloguing 第三人称单数: catalogs/catalogues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('engine', '[\'endʒɪn]', 'n.发动机；引擎；机车；火车头 vt.给 ... 装引擎', '1. What\'s the cubic capacity of this engine? 这台发动机的立体容积是多少？ 2. There must be something wrong with the engine of my car. 我汽车的引擎一定是出故障了。 3. Industrialization is the most important engine of economic growth. 工业化是经济增长最重要的拉动因素。 4. There was a puff of steam from the engine before it stopped. 机车喷出一股蒸气后就停了下来。', '过去式: engined 过去分词: engined 现在分词: engining 第三人称单数: engines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wit', '[wɪt]', 'n.智力；才智；机智；风趣 v.<古>知道；即', '1. Wit is the lowest form of humor. 智力是幽默的最低形式。 2. His character is a combination of wit and kindness. 他的性格是智慧与善良的结合。 3. Sloth tarnishes the edge of wit. 懒散能磨去才智的锋芒。 4. He gave me a taste of his acid wit. 他让我尝到了他敏锐尖刻之机智的滋味。 5. He will leave at the end of term, to wit 30 July. 他要在期末离开，也就是7月30日。', '过去式: wist 过去分词: wist 现在分词: witting 第三人称单数: wot');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('storey', '[\'stɔːri]', 'n.楼层 =story（美）.', '1. That man is a little wrong in the upper storey. 那人的头脑有些不正常。 2. The workers complete a storey in a couple of days. 一幢大楼没有多少天就盖起来了。 3. Our ten - storey building is out of straight. 我们那幢10层大楼倾斜了。 4. There be a building ten storey high by the road . 路旁有一座十层高的楼房。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('standard', '[\'stændərd]', 'n.标准；规格；水准；军旗 adj.标准的；普通的；规范的；权威的', '1. There is no absolute standard for beauty. 美是没有绝对的标准的。 2. More than 300 watches are not up to standard. 有300多块手表不合质量标准。 3. The government has an official standard for the purity of silver. 政府对于银的纯度定有官方的规格。 4. Washing machines have standard measurements to fit under kitchen units. 洗衣机的长宽高都有一定的规格，这样才能和厨房家具成为一体。 5. According to my height, what is my standard weight? 根据我的身高,我的标准体重是多少?', '副词: standardly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tension', '[\'tenʃn]', 'n.紧张；拉力；张力；紧张状态；[电]电压 vt.使拉紧；使绷紧', '1. The tension is building up. 形势逐步紧张起来。 2. The tension soon transmitted itself to all the members of the crowd. 这种紧张情绪很快感染了人群中所有的人。 3. A positive-stress component means tension. 正应力分量表示拉力。 4. If a wire is held under tension, it gets slightly longer. 电线在拉力状态下会变得略微长点。', '形容词: tensional 过去式: tensioned 过去分词: tensioned 现在分词: tensioning 第三人称单数: tensions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('semiconductor', '[ˌsemikən\'dʌktər]', 'n.半导体', '1. This is a semiconductor integrated circuit. 这是一个半导体集成电路。 2. Xi\'an IR Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. Ltd. 西安爱尔半导体制造有限公司。', '形容词: semiconducting');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('axe', '[æks]', 'n.斧；解雇；倒闭 vt.用斧砍；解雇；大量削减', '1. The heavy axe was awkward to use. 这把重斧头不好用。 2. The man cleft a block of wood in two with an axe. 那人用斧头把一块木头劈成两半。 3. A lot of people in shipbuilding will get the axe. 造船业的很多人将被解雇。 4. Patients are delighted their local hospital has been saved from the axe. 病人高兴的是当地医院获挽救免遭关闭。 5. Jones has been axed from the team. 琼斯已被开除出队。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trench', '[trentʃ]', 'n.沟；沟渠；战壕 v.挖沟；侵占', '1. The farmers gouged out a trench across the field. 农民们挖了一条穿过田野的沟。 2. They dig trench to keep the forest fire from spread. 他们挖沟以阻止森林大火蔓延。 3. I forgot to dig a trench around the tent. 我忘了在帐篷四周挖一条沟。 4. They toiled all day digging the trench. 他们整天艰苦地挖壕沟。 5. The troops received orders to trench the outpost. 部队接到命令在前哨周围筑壕加强防卫。', '过去式: trenched 过去分词: trenched 现在分词: trenching 第三人称单数: trenches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eager', '[\'iːɡər]', 'adj.热切的；渴望的', '1. He is eager for you to meet his friends. 他热切希望你见见他的朋友。 2. Eager fans mobbed the popular singer. 热切的歌迷们团团围住住这位流行歌手 3. The boys listened to my story with eager attention. 男孩们以热切的心情非常注意地倾听我的故事。 4. He was eager to see her. 他渴望见到她。', '副词: eagerly 比较级: eagerer 最高级: eagerest 名词: eagerness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('furnish', '[\'fɜːrnɪʃ]', 'vt.布置；装备；提供', '1. They are renting a furnished flat. 他们租用了一套带有家具的公寓房子。 2. We propose to furnish our own house according to our own taste. 我们建议按自己的爱好布置自己的房子。 3. They scouted around for some antiques to furnish their new apartment. 他们到处搜罗一些古董来装饰新居。 4. I am bound to furnish my antagonists with arguments, but not with comprehension. 我一定要向对手提供争论点，但并无予以理解的必要。', '名词: furnisher 过去式: furnished 过去分词: furnished 现在分词: furnishing 第三人称单数: furnishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('texture', '[\'tekstʃər]', 'n.质地；手感；口感；组织；结构；纹理；特点 vt.给予结构', '1. This kind of cloth has a close texture. 这种布质地很紧密。 2. We could feel the smooth texture of silk. 我们能感觉出丝绸的光滑质地。 3. The texture of the rug was very soft. 毯子的手感非常柔软。 4. The cake has a nice light texture. 这蛋糕松软可口。', '形容词: textural 副词: texturally 过去式: textured 过去分词: textured 现在分词: texturing 第三人称单数: textures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('theft', '[θeft]', 'n.偷窃', '1. Avarice drove him into theft. 贪婪驱使他偷窃。 2. The building has been insured against fire and theft. 这座大楼保了火险和失窃险。 3. The prosecutor brought an accusation of theft against him. 检察官指控他偷窃。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prejudice', '[\'predʒudɪs]', 'n.偏见；伤害 vt.伤害；使 ... 存偏见；使偏袒', '1. She has a prejudice against modern music. 她对现代音乐怀有偏见。 2. A judge must be free from prejudice. 法官必须不抱成见。 3. The offer was accepted without prejudice to the current pay negotiations. 该提议获得接纳，但对目前正在进行的工资谈判并无影响。 4. A new law has been brought in to discourage racial prejudice. 一项反对种族歧视的新法律已被提出。 5. Your bad spelling may prejudice your chances of getting this job. 你糟糕的拼写会妨碍你获得这个工作的机会。', '过去式: prejudiced 过去分词: prejudiced 现在分词: prejudicing 第三人称单数: prejudices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('audit', '[\'ɔːdɪt]', 'n.审计；查帐 vt.旁听；审计', '1. As usual, the yearly audit will take place in December. 跟往常一样，年度审计将在十二月份进行。 2. They work non-stop to finish the audit on time. 他们不停地工作以按期完成审计工作。 3. He had read the audit chief\'s report about the embezzlement and cash loss. 他已读过查帐部主任关于这件贪污加现款盗窃案的报告。 4. But everyone was there, helping to examine the bank\'s records for the special audit Mr. Bell was taking. 但是每个人都在那儿，帮助检查银行的记录，因为贝尔先生正在进行特别查帐。 5. Which course do you want to audit? 你想旁听哪门课?', '过去式: audited 过去分词: audited 现在分词: auditing 第三人称单数: audits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scatter', '[\'skætər]', 'vt.散播；撒；驱散 vi.分散；消散 n.散布；零星少量', '1. She wanted us to scatter her ashes to the winds. 她希望我们把她的骨灰散播到风中。 2. The farmers were scattering seed on the fields. 农夫把种子撒在田里。 3. Let\'s try not to scatter food or drink on the table. 别把饭或汤撒到桌上。 4. The police scattered the crowd. 警察驱散了人群。 5. Small villages scatter at the foot of the mountain. 村庄零零落落地散布在山脚下。 6. She gave the soup a quick scatter of herbs. 她把香料快速撒在汤上。', '名词: scatterer 过去式: scattered 过去分词: scattered 现在分词: scattering 第三人称单数: scatters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('descent', '[dɪ\'sent]', 'n.下降；下坡；家世；血统；侵袭；衰落；继承', '1. There was a descent of temperature after rain. 雨后气温下降了。 2. The trail zigzagged down the abrupt descent of the canyon. 这条小路弯弯曲曲的顺着峡谷那陡削的下坡蜿蜒而下。 3. He traces his descent back to an old norman family. 他追踪自己的世系上溯至一个古老的诺曼家族。 4. Many Americans are of English descent. 许多美国人的祖籍是英国。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outrage', '[\'aʊtreɪdʒ]', 'n.暴行；愤怒；义愤 vt.凌辱；激怒', '1. The Government has been dilatory in condemning the outrage. 政府迟迟才谴责是次暴行。 2. We should never forget the outrage committed by the Japanese invaders. 我们永远都不应该忘记日本侵略者犯下的暴行。 3. All right-minded people will be surely shocked by this outrage. 凡是有正义感的人都一定会对这种暴行感到震惊。 4. Her answer was greeted with cries of outrage. 她的回答引起了一片愤怒的吼叫。 5. He was outraged by their behavior. 他们的行为使他感到愤慨。', '过去式: outraged 过去分词: outraged 现在分词: outraging 第三人称单数: outrages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('o\'clock', '[ə\'klɒk]', '（=of the clock） ... 点钟', '1. Hello. I\'d like to reserve a table for two for eight o\' clock, please. 你好，我要订一张今晚八点两个人的餐桌。 2. It\'s eleven o\'clock now. 现在是十一点钟。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('iron', '[\'aɪərn]', 'n.熨斗；铁；刚强 (复）irons: 镣铐. v.熨；烫 adj.铁的；刚强的', '1. The iron hissed as it pressed the wet cloth. 熨斗压在湿布上时发出嘶嘶声。 2. They analyzed the ore and found iron in it. 他们分析了矿砂,从中发现了铁。 3. Tom didn\'t iron his shirt yesterday. 汤姆昨天没有熨衬衣。 4. How can I remove the rust from the iron door? 我怎样才能把铁门上的锈除掉呢？', '过去式: ironed 过去分词: ironed 现在分词: ironing 第三人称单数: irons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('memo', '[\'memoʊ]', 'n.备忘录', '1. She ticked off the items on the memo. 她在备忘录上的项目作了记号。 2. Please distribute the memo to all of the employees. 请把这备忘录发给每个员工。 3. Give a memo summarizing what you have done by the end of the week. 在本周末做一份备忘录，简要说明你的工作。', '名词复数: memos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blanket', '[\'blæŋkɪt]', 'n.毛毯；覆盖物；排字版 vt.覆盖；用毯子裹；扑灭；挡风；使包含 adj.包含所有的；适用于所有情形的', '1. He threw a blanket over the injured man. 他急忙给受伤的人披上条毯子。 2. They cuddled up (together) under the blanket. 他们盖著毯子(在一起)搂著。 3. The nurse carried in a baby wrapped (up) in a warm blanket. 保母抱著个孩子进来，孩子身上裹著暖暖的毯子。 4. The ground was covered by a thick blanket of snow. 地面上覆盖着厚厚的一层雪。 5. The countryside was blanketed with snow/fog. 乡村被雪[雾]覆盖著。 6. A blanket insurance policy insures a car against all kinds of accidents. 一张综合保险单担保汽车一切意外事件。', '过去式: blanketed 过去分词: blanketed 现在分词: blanketing 第三人称单数: blankets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cease', '[siːs]', 'v.终止；停止 n.停止', '1. He was going to cease working for them. 他将不再为他们干活。 2. When can we cease from our labours? 我们什么时候才能免除劳役之苦? 3. The old man ceased breathing the night before. 老人前一天晚上停止了呼吸。 4. The newspaper had ceased publication. 报纸已停刊。 5. We worked without cease to get the project finished on time. 我们不停地生产以便按时完成计划', '过去式: ceased 过去分词: ceased 现在分词: ceasing 第三人称单数: ceases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assign', '[ə\'saɪn]', 'vt.分配；指定；指派；归因；确定 n.受让人', '1. All the students are assigned to suitable jobs. 所有的学生都分到了合适的工作。 2. For example, you might assign each order a unique order number. 例如,可能会为每个订单分配一个唯一的订单号。 3. After establishing roles, you can assign individual users to a role. 建立角色后,可以将各个用户分配到角色。 4. For each class, you have to assign an instance name. 对于每个类,您都必须指定一个实例名称。', '形容词: assignable 副词: assignably 名词: assignability 过去式: assigned 过去分词: assigned 现在分词: assigning 第三人称单数: assigns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('neighbor', '[\'neɪbə]', 'n.邻居；邻国 v.邻近', '1. It was a neighbor he knew only socially. 这位邻居跟他只是泛泛之交。 2. My neighbor is a man of highest virtue. 我的邻居是一个具有高尚品德的人。 3. She resigned her children to the care of a neighbor. 她委托邻居照顾她的孩子。 4. I borrowed a mower from my neighbor to cut grass in my garden. 我从邻居那借了割草机来割花园里的草。 5. The garden neighbors on a golf-course. 那花园与高尔夫球场相邻。', '过去式: neighbored 过去分词: neighbored 现在分词: neighboring 第三人称单数: neighbors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('the', '[ðə]', 'art.那；这；这些；那些 adv.（用于比较级前）更加；用于最高级前；(用于形容词、副词比较级前)越 ... 越 ...', '1. I reached the gate that opened towards the lake. 我走到临湖而开的那扇门前。 2. Is it necessary for me to attend the meeting? 我真的必须参加这个会议吗？ 3. The electrical installations are very old. 这些装置那么残旧。 4. Don\'t worry. The dangerous criminals have all been locked up. 别担心,那些危险的犯罪分子都被关起来了。 5. I want the larger television. 我想要那台较大的电视机。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pebble', '[\'pebl]', 'n.鹅卵石 n.水晶；水晶透镜 v.用卵石铺；用卵石投掷；使有卵石纹', '1. On the way, Hansel dropped a pebble every several meters. 一路上，亨舍儿每隔几米就扔一块鹅卵石。 2. The son put his hand into the moneybag and drew out a pebble. 儿子把手伸进钱袋中，拿出了一粒鹅卵石。', '形容词: pebbly 过去式: pebbled 过去分词: pebbled 现在分词: pebbling 第三人称单数: pebbles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('airport', '[\'erpɔːrt]', 'n.机场；航空站', '1. The plane circled the airport before landing. 飞机在着陆之前在机场上空盘旋。 2. There was a great outcry about the construction of the new airport. 公众强烈反对修建该机场。 3. You must arrive at the airport two hours early. 你必须提前两小时到达机场。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('occupy', '[\'ɑːkjupaɪ]', 'vt.占用；占领；从事；使忙碌；专心', '1. Is that seat occupied? 那个座位有人吗？ 2. Reading occupies most of my free time. 阅读占去了我大部分的闲暇时间。 3. We occupy the farm and raise a lot of poultry. 我们拥有这个农场并养着许多家禽。 4. The enemy occupied the town. 敌人占据了这个城镇。', '名词: occupier 过去式: occupied 过去分词: occupied 现在分词: occupying 第三人称单数: occupies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('toy', '[tɔɪ]', 'n.玩具', '1. He was appointed to superintend the toy department. 他获任玩具部的负责人。 2. The child clutched his toy. 那个孩子紧抓着他的玩具不放。', '过去式: toyed 过去分词: toyed 现在分词: toying 第三人称单数: toys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chin', '[tʃɪn]', 'n.颏；下巴 v.聊天；作引体向上', '1. He gashed his chin badly when shaving. 他修面时把颏部刮破。 2. He rubbed his chin thoughtfully. 他抚摩著下巴，陷入沉思。 3. You\'ve got a cut on your chin. 你下巴上有一道伤口。 4. She caught him a blow on the chin. 她打了他下巴一拳。 5. His wife loves to make chin music. 他的老婆最喜欢聊天。', '形容词: chinless 过去式: chinned 过去分词: chinned 现在分词: chinning 第三人称单数: chins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('harmony', '[\'hɑːrməni]', 'n.和谐；协调；调和；和声', '1. An enterprise should be full of fairness and harmony. 一个企业内部应该充满公平与和谐。 2. Their life is a natural harmony. 他们的生活是一种自然的和谐。 3. There was not much harmony in international affairs during those years. 那些年国际事态不很协调。 4. Almost unconsciously she dressed in harmony with this note of simplicity. 她简直不自觉的打扮得跟这朴素的调子很调和。', '名词复数: harmonies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rouse', '[raʊz]', 'v.唤醒；激起 n.觉醒；奋起', '1. These words seemed to rouse Uncle Vernon. 这句话似乎唤醒了弗农姨父。 2. He\'s very hard to rouse in the morning. 他早晨很难被唤醒。 3. I was roused by the sound of the bell this morning. 今天早晨，我被铃声唤醒。 4. The speaker was trying to rouse the audience to enthusiasm. 那位演讲者正设法激起听众的热情。 5. At the same time,our senses remain responsive enough so that extreme external stimuli can rouse us to wakefulness. 同时，我们的感官能力，所以外界极其强烈的刺激能将我们唤醒进入觉醒状态。', '名词: rouser 过去式: roused 过去分词: roused 现在分词: rousing 第三人称单数: rouses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('omit', '[ə\'mɪt]', 'vt.省略；遗漏；忘记；删去', '1. In writing telegrams omit superfluous words. 写电报稿要省去不必要的文字。 2. I could omit the overseas section at this point. 我可以暂时把海外部分省略掉。 3. Don\'t omit his name from the list. 名单上不要遗漏了他的名字。 4. Don\'t omit locking the door. 别忘了锁门。', '过去式: omitted 过去分词: omitted 现在分词: omitting 第三人称单数: omits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('possible', '[\'pɑːsəbl]', 'adj.可能的；尽可能的；合理的 n.适合候选的人', '1. I\'ll do everything possible to help you. 我会尽一切可能帮助你。 2. It isn\'t remotely possible that you will be chosen to go. 挑选你去的可能性并非很小。 3. You\'d better rest as much as possible. 你要尽可能多休息。 4. As I\'m going on a diet, I have to eat as little as possible. 我正在节食,得尽量少吃。', '副词: possibly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whisper', '[\'wɪspər]', 'n.低语；窃窃私语；飒飒的声音 vi.低声说；窃窃私语；飒飒地响 vt.耳语；私语', '1. There is no word, no whisper, no cry. 这里没有消息，没有低语，没有呼唤。 2. She said it in a whisper, so I didn\'t hear. 她是悄声说的，所以我没有听见。 3. I heard the whisper of wind in the pines. 我听见风吹过松林间飒飒作响。 4. The children were whispering in the corner. 孩子们正在角落里低声耳语。 5. Fatso leaned over to whisper in her ear. 胖子欠身对她耳语几句。', '形容词: whispery 名词: whisperer 过去式: whispered 过去分词: whispered 现在分词: whispering 第三人称单数: whispers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('behind', '[bɪ\'haɪnd]', 'prep.在...之后；迟于...；落后于；基于；追赶 adv.在后面地；落后地；迟；不如 n.<口> 屁股', '1. Who is the girl standing behind Richard? 站在理查德后面的那个姑娘是谁？ 2. The train was 10 minutes behind time. 火车晚到了十分钟。 3. Britain is behind Japan in developing modern technologies. 在发展现代技术方面英国落后于日本。 4. Behind your every action is self-interest. 你的每一行动都出于个人私利。 5. He caught up with the parade and walked behind. 他赶上了游行队伍，跟在后面走。 6. Little Tom gave him a kick in the behind. 小汤姆在他屁股上踢了一脚。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('explicit', '[ɪk\'splɪsɪt]', 'adj.明确的；清晰的；清楚的；露骨的', '1. They gave explicit reasons for leaving. 他们明确地说出了离开的原因。 2. A man can try his best to perfect and improve himself only if he has strong desires and explicit goal. 只有怀着强烈的欲望,有着明确的目标,一个人才能竭尽全力去完善自我,提升自我。 3. He has an explicit understanding of this. 他对这个了解得很清晰。 4. He gave me explicit directions on how to get there. 他清清楚楚地告诉我怎样到达那里。', '副词: explicitly 名词: explicitness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('substance', '[\'sʌbstəns]', 'n.实质；物质；财产；内容；重要性', '1. The Substance and Prospect of \"East China Sea\" Dispute between China and Japan 中日\"东海问题\"的实质及展望 2. The emery is a hard metallic substance. 金刚砂是非常坚硬的金属物质。 3. Beware of what you do with this dangerous substance. 你处理这些危险品时，可要当心。 4. Later he became a man of substance. 后来，他成为颇具资产的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pamphlet', '[\'pæmflət]', 'n.小册子', '1. He gave me a pamphlet for my call numbers. 他给了我一个小册子记录电话号码。 2. The pamphlet was written to his party. 这本小册子是特地为他的政党所写的。', '形容词: pamphletary');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('friendly', '[\'frendli]', 'adj.友好的；友善的 adv.友好地', '1. The meeting is gone on in very friendly atmosphere. 会议在非常友好的气氛中进行。 2. He cloaked his evil purpose under friendly words. 他用友好的语言来掩盖他罪恶的目的。 3. He was not very friendly to us. 他对我们不太友善。 4. Our neighbourhood police are very friendly. 我们邻近的警察非常友善。 5. Let\'s keep the conversation on a friendly plane. 让我们友好地谈话。', '副词: friendlily 比较级: friendlier 最高级: friendliest 名词: friendliness 名词复数: friendlies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('none', '[nʌn]', 'pron.没有人；没有任何东西，一个也没有，毫无 adv.决不', '1. None could produce a simple, tidy answer. 没有人能提出一个简单而又令人满意的答案。 2. None of us like to go skate in winter. 我们之中没有人愿意在冬天去滑冰。 3. None of them dares even mutter dissent. 没有人敢说半个不字。 4. I wanted some string but there was none in the house. 我需要一些绳子，但家里一根也没有。 5. My car is none the worse for the accident. 我的汽车遇到事故，但毫无损坏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abandon', '[ə\'bændən]', 'v.放弃；抛弃；放纵 n.放纵', '1. Those who abandon themselves to despair can not succeed. 那些自暴自弃的人无法成功。 2. Despite some difficulties, they\'re not going to abandon the plan. 尽管他们遇到了一些困难,但并不打算放弃这个计划。 3. The cruel man abandoned his wife and child. 那个狠心的男人抛弃了他的妻儿。 4. They abandon themselves to drinking. 他们沉湎于饮酒。 5. He signed cheques with careless abandon. 他无所顾忌地乱开支票。', '名词: abandonment 过去式: abandoned 过去分词: abandoned 现在分词: abandoning 第三人称单数: abandons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('monument', '[\'mɑːnjumənt]', 'n.纪念碑；历史遗迹；不朽作品', '1. The monument was fronted with stone. 纪念碑的正面是石料做的。 2. Nelson\'s Column is a famous monument in London. 纳尔逊纪念碑是伦敦著名的纪念碑。 3. The monument is in honor of a scientist. 那座纪念碑是为纪念一位科学家而建的。 4. Time and weather had long ago effaced the inscription on the monument. 岁月和风雨早已磨掉纪念碑上的铭文。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contradiction', '[ˌkɑːntrə\'dɪkʃn]', 'n.矛盾；反驳；否认；不一致', '1. Motion itself is a contradiction. 运动本身就是矛盾。 2. The contradiction was only apparent. 那矛盾只是表面上的。 3. The contradiction has become apparent. 矛盾表面化了。 4. This contradiction is hushed up . 这个矛盾消除了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('novel', '[\'nɑːvl]', 'n.小说 adj.新奇的', '1. The novel is considered a brilliant performance. 这部小说被认为是出色的佳作。 2. I like reading novels in my spare time. 我喜欢闲暇时读小说。 3. This film is based on a novel by D.H.Lawrence. 这部影片是根据D. 4. It\'s a novel idea. 那是个异常的想法。', '副词: novelly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('harm', '[hɑːrm]', 'n.危害；伤害；损害 vt.伤害；损害', '1. If we interfere, it may do more harm than good. 倘若我们进行干预，那可能弊多利少。 2. It wouldn\'t do him any harm to work a bit harder. 工作努力点对他没什么害处。 3. The army defends the people from harm . 军队保护人民免遭伤害。 4. His failures did his reputation a lot of harm. 他屡次失败使他的声誉受到很大损害。 5. There was a traffic accident in this street, but no one was harmed. 这街上发生了交通事故，但没有人受伤。', '过去式: harmed 过去分词: harmed 现在分词: harming 第三人称单数: harms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('satisfactory', '[ˌsætɪs\'fæktəri]', 'adj.令人满意的', '1. The efficacy of the medicine is satisfactory. 这药的药效令人满意。 2. His general state of health is fairly satisfactory. 他总的健康状况相当令人满意。 3. You must accept the result, satisfactory or otherwise. 你必须接受这个结果，满意也好不满意也好。 4. Everything was turning out most satisfactory. 一切都非常趁心如意。', '副词: satisfactorily 名词: satisfactoriness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('direct', '[də\'rekt]', 'adj.直接的；笔直的；坦白的 v.对准；指挥；指示；命令', '1. I\' m in direct contact with the hijackers. 我与劫机者保持着直接的联系. 2. Keep product away from direct sunlight and store in a dry cool place. 置放在不受阳光直射,干燥通风的地方。 3. He is very direct, so you always know what his real views are. 他为人很直率, 所以你总能知道他的真实想法。 4. The guide directed our attention to the other picture. 讲解员要我们注意另一幅画.', '过去式: directed 过去分词: directed 现在分词: directing 第三人称单数: directs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('casual', '[\'kæʒuəl]', 'adj.非正式的；漫不经心的；偶然的；临时的；休闲的 n.便装；临时工', '1. He was wearing casual clothes. 他穿着便服。 2. The plan grew out of a casual conversation. 这个计划出自于一次非正式的谈话。 3. He sidled past, trying to seem casual. 他悄悄地溜了过去,竭力装作漫不经心的样子。 4. She is casual about winning the prize. 她对获奖漫不经心。', '副词: casually 名词: casualness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ruin', '[\'ruːɪn]', 'vt.毁灭；毁坏；（使）破产；糟蹋，使（妇女）失去贞操 n.毁灭；废墟；崩溃', '1. He ruined his prospects by carelessness. 他因疏忽大意而断送了前途。 2. The politics of the company will ruin their image. 公司的策略会毁掉他们的形象。 3. His enemies maliciously conspired to ruin him. 他的敌人恶毒地密谋搞垮他。 4. The rain ruined my painting. 这场雨把我的画给毁了。 5. His rashness led ultimately to his ruin. 他的急躁鲁莽最终导致了他的毁灭。', '形容词: ruinable 名词: ruiner 过去式: ruined 过去分词: ruined 现在分词: ruining 第三人称单数: ruins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('layout', '[\'leɪaʊt]', 'n.安排；布局；设计', '1. The designer chooses the layout of reinforcement. 设计者选择钢筋布置。 2. You will be asked to choose your keyboard layout. 将让你选择键盘布局。 3. The designer chooses the layout of reinforcement. 设计者选择钢筋布置。 4. The robbers studied the layout of the bank. 这伙强盗研究了银行的布局。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('symposium', '[sɪm\'poʊziəm]', 'n.讨论会；酒会；论文集', '1. We will hold a symposium this afternoon. 今天下午，我们要召开一次讨论会。 2. In this symposium, my part is only to sit in silence. 在这次讨论会上，我只要安静的坐着就够了。', '名词复数: symposiums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reconcile', '[\'rekənsaɪl]', 'v.调和；和解；妥协；一致', '1. I can\'t reconcile the two extreme views. 我无法调和这两种极端的观点。 2. We tried to reconcile her with her family. 我们试图让她和她的家庭和好。 3. We were finally reconciled when he apologized. 他道歉以后我们终于言归于好了. 4. He had to reconcile himself to his fate. 他必须接受自己的命运。', '形容词: reconciliatory 名词: reconcilement 过去式: reconciled 过去分词: reconciled 现在分词: reconciling 第三人称单数: reconciles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elastic', '[ɪ\'læstɪk]', 'adj.灵活的；有弹性的；可变的 n.橡皮圈；有松紧的东西', '1. The new policy was sufficiently elastic to accommodate both views. 新政策充分灵活地适用两种观点。 2. Rubber is elastic. 橡皮是有弹性的。 3. This swimming costume is made of elastic material. 这件游泳衣是由弹性材料做成的。 4. The slacks have an elastic waistband. 这条便裤的腰带可伸缩。 5. It snapped back like a piece of elastic. 它像一条橡皮带那样迅速弹回。', '副词: elastically 名词: elasticity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tear', '[ter]', 'vt.撕掉；扯下；扰乱 vi.流泪；撕破 n.眼泪；（撕破的）洞或裂缝；撕扯', '1. Take the book from Alice, she will tear it. 把书从艾丽斯那拿开，她会撕了它的。 2. Nails that project may tear your clothes. 突出的钉子会刮坏你的衣服。 3. Her heart was torn by anxiety. 她焦虑得心都快碎了。 4. Don began to tear up when he talked about his son. 唐谈论起他的儿子就开始哭。 5. My wife burst into tears when she heard the bad news. 我太太听到这个坏消息就哭了起来。', '名词: tearer 过去式: tore 过去分词: torn 现在分词: tearing 第三人称单数: tears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('famous', '[\'feɪməs]', 'adj.著名的；有名的', '1. New York is famous for its skyscrapers. 纽约以其摩天大楼著称。 2. Oscar Wilde was a famous wit. 奥斯卡·王尔德是个著名的风趣的人。 3. The parks of this city are famous for their ornate fountains. 这个城市的公园以其华丽的喷泉而著名。 4. He is a very famous writer in this country. 他是这个国家里很有名的作家。', '副词: famously 名词: famousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aircraft', '[\'erkræft]', 'n.飞机', '1. The wings of the aircraft had iced up. 机翼上结了一层冰。 2. A large passenger aircraft will land on the airfield. 一架大型民航班机将降落在这个飞机场。 3. Only experienced pilots fly large passenger aircraft. 只有有经验的飞行员才能驾驶大型客机。 4. The watchtower followed the aircraft by radar. 瞭望塔通过雷达追踪这架飞机的行踪。', '名词复数: aircraft');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('million', '[\'mɪljən]', 'n.百万；群众 adj.无数的；百万的', '1. It is estimated that the damage was over one million dollars. 据估计，损失超过了一百万元。 2. The old man left an estate of two million dollars when he died. 那老人去世时留下二百万美元的遗产。 3. There were millions of people in the square. 广场上有好多好多人。', '名词复数: million');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sweat', '[swet]', 'n.汗水 n.焦急；繁重工作；(凝结在物体表面的)水珠 v.(使)出汗', '1. He is covered with sweat. 他浑身是汗。 2. Camel, soaked with sweat, makes a hand expression for \"shush\" secretly. 满身大汗的卡梅尔悄悄地做出一个“嘘”的手势。 3. She stood up to wipe the sweat off her face. 她站起来擦擦脸上的汗珠。 4. Sweat was pouring down his face. 他满头大汗。 5. I was all of a sweat before the exam. 我临考前急得不得了. 6. The long climb made us sweat. 我们攀登了很长距离，已大汗淋漓了。', '过去式: sweated/sweat 过去分词: sweated/sweat 现在分词: sweating 第三人称单数: sweats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('damage', '[\'dæmɪdʒ]', 'n.损害；损失；毁坏 vt.损害；毁坏', '1. The damage to the painting is the work of vandals. 毁坏这幅画的事是恣意破坏公物的人干的。 2. Knowing all this, they made me pay for the damage. 他们尽管了解这一切,还是让我赔偿损失。 3. The flood did a lot of damage to the crops. 洪水毁坏了大量农作物。 4. Drinking and smoking can damage your health. 饮酒和吸烟会损害你的健康。', '形容词: damageable 副词: damagingly 名词: damageability 过去式: damaged 过去分词: damaged 现在分词: damaging 第三人称单数: damages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sandwich', '[\'sænwɪtʃ]', 'n.三明治 vt.插入；夹在中间', '1. I had a ham sandwich as lunch. 我吃了一个火腿三明治作午餐。 2. I\'ll try a chicken salad sandwich. 我想尝尝鸡肉色拉三明治。 3. I\'m busy today but I will sandwich that job after supper. 今天我很忙，但我会在晚饭后挤出时间干那件事。 4. He was sandwiched between two fat women on the bus. 他在公共汽车上被夹在两个胖女人中间。', '过去式: sandwiched 过去分词: sandwiched 现在分词: sandwiching 第三人称单数: sandwiches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('segment', '[\'seɡmənt]', 'n.部分；弓形；瓣；段；节 vt.分割', '1. The company dominates this segment of the market. 这家公司控制了这一部分市场。 2. She cleaned a small segment of the painting. 她把画儿上的一小部分擦干净了。 3. The waiter brought us a dish of orange segments. 服务员给我们端来一盘掰开的橘子瓣。 4. Essentially, each segment is its own address space. 从本质上来说,每个段就是自己的地址空间。 5. Do you know how to segment an orange? 你知道怎么切橙子吗?', '形容词: segmentary 过去式: segmented 过去分词: segmented 现在分词: segmenting 第三人称单数: segments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('partner', '[\'pɑːrtnər]', 'n.伙伴；搭档；伴侣；合伙人 v.同 ... 合作；做 ... 的搭档', '1. He has a competent partner who always organizes everything well for him. 他有个很能干的伙伴,总是替他把一切弄得井井有条。 2. Will you be my partner in the next dance? 下一支曲子时可否请你跟我一起跳舞? 3. I am so lucky to have a partner like you to enjoy the beauty of life together. 我真幸运,能拥有你这样的伴侣陪我一起享受生命中的美好。 4. Her partner tried to trick her out of her share. 她的合伙人企图骗走她的股份。 5. They have to partner with the government, even if they are dismissive of its bureaucracy. 他们同政府合作,即使他们看不惯政府的官僚主义。', '过去式: partnered 过去分词: partnered 现在分词: partnering 第三人称单数: partners');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quantity', '[\'kwɑːntəti]', 'n.量；数量；大量', '1. This company is more concerned with quality than with quantity. 这家公司对质量比对产量更重视。 2. He ate a small quantity of rice. 他吃了少量的米饭。 3. It was a bad year for films, in terms of both quantity and quality. 今年的电影无论从数量上还是质量上都说不上好。 4. In our work quality counts for as much as quantity. 在我们的工作中，质量跟数量同等重要。', '名词复数: quantities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('edit', '[\'edɪt]', 'vt.剪辑；编辑；校订', '1. You\'ll have to edit that tape, it\'s too long. 那盘录音带太长, 你得把它剪辑一下。 2. You shouldn‘t need to edit this file directly. 您不必直接编辑该文件。 3. He edit a daily paper before he come to teach at our college. 他来我们学院任教之前充任过一份日报的主编。 4. Allows the user to edit the object. 允许用户编辑对象。', '过去式: edited 过去分词: edited 现在分词: editing 第三人称单数: edits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('band', '[bænd]', 'n.乐队；队；一群 n.带；箍；波段 v.绑扎 v.联合；结合', '1. The band played a lively tune. 乐队演奏了一支轻快的乐曲。 2. The brass band is banging away in the park. 铜管乐队在公园里吹吹打打。 3. They are a teenager band made up of four cool boys. 他们是一支由四名酷哥组成的少年演唱队。 4. A band of robbers held up the train. 一群强盗抢劫了火车。 5. She used a rubber band to tie her hair. 她用一根橡皮筋扎头发。 6. If you band the bird\'s leg, you can identify it later. 如果你在鸟腿上套上标记环,以後就能认出它。 7. The children banded together to buy a present for their teacher. 孩子们合起来为他们的老师买了一件礼物。', '过去式: banded 过去分词: banded 现在分词: banding 第三人称单数: bands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shilling', '[\'ʃɪlɪŋ]', 'n.先令（货币单位）', '1. In former times, 12 pence went to a shilling. 过去，十二便士等于一先令。 2. If I give you a shilling, we shall be all square. 我给你一先令，咱们就两清了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('behalf', '[bɪ\'hæf]', 'n.代表；利益；方面', '1. The agent spoke on behalf of his principal. 代理人代表他的委托人说话。 2. On behalf of my colleagues and myself I thank you. 我代表我的同事和我本人向你表示感谢。 3. He agreed to testify on behalf of the accused man. 他同意为被告作证。 4. I put up the proposal on your behalf. 我是为你的利益才提出这个建议的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('series', '[\'sɪriːz]', 'n.（单复同）系列；丛书；连续', '1. The lecture series falls naturally into three parts. 该系列讲座可自然分作三部分。 2. The theory is based on a series of wrong assumptions. 这一理论是以一系列错误的设想为依据的。 3. He published a new series of readers for students of English. 他出版了一套新的英语学习丛书。 4. After a series of unsuccessful attempts, he has finally passed the driving test. 经过连续几次的失败，他最后终于通过了驾驶考试。', '名词复数: series');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prominent', '[\'prɑːmɪnənt]', 'adj.显著的；杰出的；突出的', '1. That school is prominent in baseball. 那个学校以棒球著称。 2. Virginia Woolf is one of the most prominent writers in English literature. 弗吉尼亚·尔夫是英国文学史中一名重要的作家。 3. Einstein was a prominent scientist. 爱因斯坦是一位卓越的科学家。 4. She is having a lean, gaunt frame with prominent bones. 他骨瘦如柴的身材又细又瘦,骨骼突出的', '副词: prominently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compulsory', '[kəm\'pʌlsəri]', 'adj.强制的；势在必行的；义务的', '1. Attendance at evening prayers is not compulsory. 参加晚祷并非硬性规定。 2. I think it is compulsory. 我认为这是非做不可的。 3. The car insurance is compulsory. 这项汽车保险是强制性的。 4. I think it is compulsory to look over the house. 我认为检查这栋房子势在必行。', '副词: compulsorily 名词: compulsoriness 名词复数: compulsories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('citizen', '[\'sɪtɪzn]', 'n.公民；市民', '1. He is a Dane inasmuch as he was born in Denmark, but he became a British citizen at the age of 30. 他按其出生在丹麦来说是丹麦人，但他在30岁时成了英国公民。 2. She is a lawful citizen. 她是个守法的公民。 3. This accusation of bribery is a vile smear on an honorable citizen. 这项有关贿赂的指控是对一个正直公民的无耻诽谤。 4. A citizen of London is called a Londoner. 伦敦的市民被叫做伦敦人。', '形容词: citizenly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bleak', '[bliːk]', 'adj.萧瑟的；阴郁的；严寒的；无希望的', '1. The bleak breeze blights the brightly blooming blossom. 萧瑟的微风吹枯了盛开着的花。 2. The bleak ground pullulated with jackrabbits. 荒凉的土地上到处是长耳大野兔。 3. The world was not always so bleak. 这个世界不是生来就如此凄冷的。 4. It\'s a bleak look-out for the coal industry as the number of pit closures increases. 煤井关闭的数目日多，煤炭工业前景暗淡。', '副词: bleakly 比较级: bleaker 最高级: bleakest 名词: bleakness 名词复数: bleak');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('classification', '[ˌklæsɪfɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.分类；类别', '1. There is a hierarchy in the classification of all living creatures. 一切生物均可按等级分类。 2. It is helpful to begin with a rough and ready classification. 首先进行粗略的分类是很有帮助的。 3. Such classification tends to detract from generality. 这样的分类方法缺乏概括性。 4. These things belong in a different classification. 这些东西属于不同的类别。', '形容词: classificatory 副词: classificatorily');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bribe', '[braɪb]', 'n.贿赂；贿赂物 v.贿赂', '1. He is so honest that he will not accept bribe. 他忠诚老实，不肯受贿。 2. There is a big stink about his accepting a bribe. 他收受贿赂，引起一场大纠纷。 3. He demeant himself by accepting a bribe. 他接受了贿赂，辱没了自己。 4. He bribed his way past the guard and escaped. 他买通看守而逃之夭夭了。', '形容词: bribable 名词: briber 过去式: bribed 过去分词: bribed 现在分词: bribing 第三人称单数: bribes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inflation', '[ɪn\'fleɪʃn]', 'n.通货膨胀；膨胀', '1. The new government\'s prime task is to reduce the level of inflation. 新政府的主要任务是减低通货膨胀的水平。 2. The determinate factor of our economy is to control inflation. 我们经济的决定性因素是控制通货膨胀。 3. Farmers suffered from the price inflation. 价格膨胀让农民受害。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lip', '[lɪp]', 'n.嘴唇；唇状物 v.接吻；说话；拍打', '1. He kissed her on the lips. 他吻了她的嘴唇。 2. She bit her lip to keep from crying. 她咬着嘴唇克制着自己不要哭。 3. After a moment\'s hesitation she lipped her request. 她犹豫了一会儿,然後轻声提出请求。', '形容词: lipless 过去式: lipped 过去分词: lipped 现在分词: lipping 第三人称单数: lips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adjust', '[ə\'dʒʌst]', 'v.调整；校准；调节；使适应', '1. Could you teach me how to adjust the iris of the camera? 你能教我怎么调照相机的光圈吗？ 2. This kind of desk can be adjusted to the height you need. 这种书桌的高低可以按照你的需要调节。 3. He can\'t adjust himself to the whirl of modern life in this big city. 他无法适应这个大都市的现代生活的忙碌。 4. Over the years, we all learned to adjust, to become more comfortable with each other, and to adapt to our new family arrangement. 年复一年，我们都学会了调整自己，学会了彼此宽容，学会了适应我们新的家庭规则。', '形容词: adjustable 副词: adjustably 名词: adjuster 过去式: adjusted 过去分词: adjusted 现在分词: adjusting 第三人称单数: adjusts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('submarine', '[ˌsʌbmə\'riːn]', 'n.潜水艇 adj.海面下的', '1. The frigate rammed the submarine. 护卫舰撞击了潜艇。 2. The ship was sunk by an atomic submarine. 这艘船是被一艘核潜艇击沉的。 3. A submarine glided silently through the water. 一艘潜水艇无声地在水中滑行。 4. At the first sign of danger the submarine will submerge. 一有危险迹象，潜艇就会潜入水中。 5. They are building a submarine cable tunnel. 他们正在建设一条海底电缆隧道。', '过去式: submarined 过去分词: submarined 现在分词: submarining 第三人称单数: submarines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prospect', '[\'prɑːspekt]', 'n.希望；前景；景色 v.勘探；寻找', '1. A rich harvest is in prospect. 丰收在望。 2. I see little prospect of an improvement in his condition. 我看他的情况没有什么改进的希望。 3. What do you think about the marketing prospect? 你觉得市场前景怎么样? 4. The prospect from the balcony was breathtaking. 从阳台上看去景色美极了。 5. They went there to prospect for gold . 他们去那儿勘探金矿。', '过去式: prospected 过去分词: prospected 现在分词: prospecting 第三人称单数: prospects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sore', '[sɔːr]', 'adj.疼痛的；痛心的；恼火的；严重的 n.痛处；伤口', '1. My legs are sore from all that running yesterday. 我的腿因为昨天跑步而感到酸痛。 2. Losing the election was a sore disappointment. 竞选失败令人痛心失望。 3. She\'s still a bit sore after the accident. 她出事后直到现在还觉得痛呢。 4. Don\'t get sore; I didn\'t mean it! 别生气，我不是故意的！ 5. He had a sore on his foot. 他的脚疼。', '比较级: sorer 最高级: sorest 名词: soreness 过去式: sored 过去分词: sored 现在分词: soring 第三人称单数: sores');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('government', '[\'ɡʌvərnmənt]', 'n.政府；政体；统治', '1. The government will garrison the coastal towns. 政府将派军驻守沿海的城镇。 2. The government would not even consider his claim for money. 政府甚至不考虑他的赔款要求。 3. He is a man of some influence in the government circles. 他是个在政府内有一定势力的人。 4. Five hundred jobs were axed as a result of government spending cuts. 由于政府缩减经费的缘故，有五百人被突然解雇了。', '形容词: governmental 副词: governmentally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outskirts', '[\'aʊtskɜːrts]', 'n.郊区 名词outskirt的复数.', '1. We live on the outskirts of the city. 我们住在这个城市的郊区。 2. The hotel is situated in the outskirts of the city. 这个酒店位于城市的郊区。 3. You may as well take a brief look at the outskirts and the city along the way. 大家不妨欣赏一下沿途郊区和市区的景色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scissors', '[\'sɪzərz]', 'n.剪刀', '1. Leonardo Da Vinci invented the scissors. 达芬奇发明了剪刀。 2. We bought some new scissors yesterday. 我们昨天买了一些新剪刀。 3. Blunt scissors don\'t cut cleanly. 钝剪刀剪不齐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('circuit', '[\'sɜːrkɪt]', 'n.巡回；线路；环形；电路；回路 v.巡回；绕 ... 环形', '1. For many years he was top banana on the circuit. 几年来,他是巡回剧团里的主角。 2. The commanding officer made a circuit of the camp. 指挥官在营地巡视一周。 3. Complete minor repairs to circuit wiring. 完成线路小修。 4. The circuit is a conventional ring counter. 此线路是一个普通的环形计数器。 5. I hit the lunch-and-lecture circuit again. 我又去参加那些巡回午餐演讲了。', '过去式: circuited 过去分词: circuited 现在分词: circuiting 第三人称单数: circuits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relish', '[\'relɪʃ]', 'v.享受；从...获得乐趣；品味；渴望；喜欢；有滋味 n.滋味；爱好；调味品', '1. Take each day and relish each moment. 认真过每一天并且好好享受每一时刻。 2. He seemed to relish the scandal. 他似乎对这件丑闻十分欣赏。 3. Take a moment and relish this with me! Soon all will be revealed! 和我一起品味这份经历吧！很快一切都会浮出水面！ 4. His wife won\'t relish having to wash all those dishes. 他的妻子不会喜欢洗这一大堆碟子的。 5. He drank up the wine with relish. 他津津有味地把酒喝光了。', '过去式: relished 过去分词: relished 现在分词: relishing 第三人称单数: relishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('him', '[hɪm]', 'pron.他(he的宾格)', '1. The accident left him with paralysis of the legs. 事故使他双腿瘫痪。 2. His blindness is a great trial to him. 眼睛瞎对他来说是非常麻烦的事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('barely', '[\'berli]', 'adv.几乎不；刚刚；勉强；少量地', '1. He is so weak that he can barely stand up. 他身体虚弱几乎站不起来。 2. I had barely started speaking when he interrupted me. 我刚刚开始讲话，他便打断了我。 3. We had barely enough money to last through the weekend. 我们的钱只能勉强维持到周末。 4. The room was barely furnished. 这个房间里陈设简陋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('medicine', '[\'medsn]', 'n.药；医学', '1. I have a stomachache. May I have some medicine? 我胃痛,能给我开点药吗? 2. The best medicine for you now would be a good holiday. 目前对你来说,一个愉快的假期就是一剂良药。 3. There have been great progresses in medicine in the past decade. 在过去十年里,医学取得了巨大的进步。 4. He turned to the study and practice of medicine at the age of 30. 他从30岁起开始从事医学的研究和应用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('teacher', '[\'tiːtʃər]', 'n.教师', '1. I asked the teacher for her advice. 我征求这位老师的意见。 2. She is a teacher aged only twenty. 她是一位年仅二十岁的教师。 3. My foreign teacher came from Australia. 我的外籍教师来自澳大利亚。 4. The maths teacher was furious and gave me 50 lines. 数学老师气坏了，罚我抄书50行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spacecraft', '[\'speɪskræft]', 'n.宇宙飞船', '1. Spacecraft have already traveled to other planets. 宇宙飞船已游览了别的行星。 2. The spacecraft is orbiting the moon. 宇宙飞船正绕月球飞行。', '名词复数: spacecraft');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('congress', '[\'kɑːŋɡrəs]', 'n.代表大会；议会 n.立法机关 n.国会<美>', '1. This matter will be discussed in congress tomorrow. 这个问题将在明天的代表大会上讨论。 2. The National People\'s Congress is the supreme organ of state power. 全国人民代表大会是最高国家权力机关。 3. The mayor must make policies in accordance with the bill passed in the Congress. 市长要根据议会的议案来制定政策。 4. A new peace initiative was approved by Mexico\'s congress. 墨西哥立法机关通过了一项最新的和平方案。', '形容词: congressional 副词: congressionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('paradigm', '[\'pærədaɪm]', 'n.范例；示范；典范；[语]词形变化表', '1. There\'s no paradigm to follow in this new industry. 在这个崭新的行业里没有范例可做参考。 2. No prevailing paradigm in science lasts forever. 科学中没有任何流行范式能够存在永远。 3. We now see paradigms and paradigm overthrows everywhere, inside of science and out. 我们现在可以随处看到典范和推翻典范的事例，无论在科学还是其他方面。 4. The Aristotelian paradigm prefers the frog perspective, whereas the Platonic paradigm prefers the bird perspective. 亚里士多德的典范偏向蛙的眼光，而柏拉图的典范偏向鸟的眼光。', '形容词: paradigmatic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('root', '[ruːt]', 'n.根；根源；根本 v.生根；扎根；根除', '1. Ann caught her foot on a tree root and stumbled. 安的一只脚被树根绊了一下跌倒了。 2. The dog is snuffling around the root of a tree. 那条狗在树根处嗅来嗅去。 3. Unhappiness is the root cause of his illness. 不开心是他生病的根源。 4. Money is thought to be the root cause of all evils. 金钱被认为是万恶之源。 5. Roses will not root in such acid soil. 玫瑰在这种酸性土壤中不会生根。', '名词: rooter 过去式: rooted 过去分词: rooted 现在分词: rooting 第三人称单数: roots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('copper', '[\'kɑːpər]', 'n.铜；铜币；警察；紫铜色；有紫铜色翅膀的小蝴蝶 vt.镀铜', '1. Copper conducts electricity better than iron does. 铜的导电性比铁强。 2. The shop sells copper vessels of all shapes. 这家商店出售各种形状的铜器皿。 3. He polished up the old copper coins. 他把旧铜币擦亮。 4. I gave him a few coppers. 我给了他几个铜币。 5. Zinc base die castings are always copper plated in cyanide baths. 锌基合金的压铸件总是在氰化镀液中镀铜。', '形容词: coppery 过去式: coppered 过去分词: coppered 现在分词: coppering 第三人称单数: coppers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('possession', '[pə\'zeʃn]', 'n.拥有；财产；所有；殖民地', '1. He was found in possession of dangerous drugs. 她被发现藏有危险物品。 2. We\'ve bought the house, but we can\'t get possession of it before July. 我们买下了这所房子, 但要到七月份才算实际拥有。 3. The people had to gather up their few possessions and escaped abroad. 人们不得不收拾起仅有的一点财物逃到国外去。 4. The villa is in the mayor\'s possession. 那幢别墅属镇长所有。', '形容词: possessional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('climb', '[klaɪm]', 'v.攀登；爬；上升 n.爬；攀爬处', '1. I have some climbing plants in the garden. 我的花园里长着一些攀缘植物。 2. We go to climb mountains every Sunday. 每个星期天我们都去爬山。 3. The road climbs steeply for several miles. 这条路有几英里向上倾斜得很陡。 4. The value of imports has climbed sharply in the last year. 去年进口货物的价值急剧上升。 5. Do you think you can climb that steep cliff? 你以为你能爬上那座悬崖峭壁吗？', '形容词: climbable 过去式: climbed 过去分词: climbed 现在分词: climbing 第三人称单数: climbs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hole', '[hoʊl]', 'n.洞；孔；穴；漏洞；困境 v.挖洞；掘坑；进洞', '1. There is a hole in my sock. 我的袜子上有个洞。 2. The dog skins through the small hole in the wall. 那条狗勉强钻过小小的墙洞。 3. He chiseled a hole in the door to fit a new lock. 他在门上凿了个孔，以便装一把新锁。 4. The hunters blocked up the hole of the beast. 猎人堵住了兽穴。 5. They will hole a tunnel through the mountain. 他们将穿山打隧道。', '过去式: holed 过去分词: holed 现在分词: holing 第三人称单数: holes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ideology', '[ˌaɪdi\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.意识形态；空论；观念学', '1. An obsolete ideology can hamper an economy. 过时的意识形态会束缚经济。 2. Nothing lay outside the scheme of our ideology. 我们的意识形态领域包罗万象。 3. Consensus came at the cost of ideology. 共识是通过放弃意识形态立场而获得的。 4. His attitude to ownership is rooted in communist ideology. 他的所有制观点源自共产主义思想。', '名词: ideologist 名词复数: ideologies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('amiable', '[\'eɪmiəbl]', 'adj.和蔼的；亲切的', '1. The amiable countenance of Mr. Pickwick was fast recovering its customary expression. 匹克威克先生的和蔼的脸孔在很快地恢复着平常的表情。 2. The hostess received her friends with an amiable smile. 女主人带着亲切的微笑迎接朋友们的到来。 3. You can sort out any differences you have in an amiable manner. 你可以以温柔亲切的主式澄清所有的误会。', '副词: amiably 名词: amiability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ride', '[raɪd]', 'v.骑；乘 n.交通工具；骑；乘车；搭便车', '1. She hasn\'t been out riding since the accident. 她自从出了事故以后，一直没有骑马外出过。 2. I can ride a bicycle, and I can drive a car, but I can not ride a horse. 我会骑自行车，而且我会开汽车。但我不会骑马。 3. You\'ll never learn to ride a bicycle if you don\'t practise. 如果你不练习,就学不会骑自行车。 4. It\'s a ten-minute ride on the bus. 乘公共汽车要用十分钟。 5. A park and ride network will allow private vehicles to also act as feeders to the rail system. 泊车转乘网络将有助于私家车成为接驳铁路的交通工具。', '过去式: rode 过去分词: ridden 现在分词: riding 第三人称单数: rides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conscious', '[\'kɑːnʃəs]', 'adj.神志清醒的；意识到的；自觉的；有意的 n.意识', '1. His rudeness was conscious, not accidental. 他的粗暴无礼是故意的,不是偶然的。 2. He was conscious of his guilt. 他自知有罪。 3. I am conscious that I have done right. 我相信自己做得不错。 4. I had to make a conscious effort not to be rude to him. 我得刻意约束自己不要对他粗鲁。 5. ou avoid conflict between your conscious and subconscious in the sleepy state. 在你处于昏昏欲睡状态时，你要避免你的表意识和潜意识之间的冲突。', '副词: consciously');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('differentiate', '[ˌdɪfə\'renʃieɪt]', 'vt.区分；使差异；求导数 vi.区别；产生差别；区别对待', '1. Can you differentiate one variety from the other? 你能将这两个品种区别开来吗? 2. He cannot differentiate the two flowers. 他无法辨认这两种花。 3. The only way to differentiate yourself from the competition is through service. 只有服务才能真正使你在竞争中凸显。 4. I cannot differentiate between these two things. 我无法区别这两个东西。', '名词: differentiation 过去式: differentiated 过去分词: differentiated 现在分词: differentiating 第三人称单数: differentiates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('instead', '[ɪn\'sted]', 'adv.代替；反而', '1. I gave him advice instead of money. 我给了他忠告，而不是钱。 2. I made this cake specially, with brown sugar instead of white. 我特别地以红糖代替白糖做了这个蛋糕。 3. We shouldn\'t look down upon them, instead we should try to help them and take more care of them. 我们不仅不该歧视他们,反而更要多帮助、照顾他们。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unusual', '[ʌn\'juːʒuəl]', 'adj.异常的；独特的；与众不同的', '1. I look on the matter as most unusual. 我认为这件事极不寻常。 2. Something unusual was about to happen. 某种不寻常的事正要发生。 3. Mr. Heath was a man of unusual character. 希思先生具有独特的个性。 4. Her unusual utterance revealed her emotions. 她不同寻常的语调暴露出她的感情。', '副词: unusually 名词: unusualness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cement', '[sɪ\'ment]', 'n.水泥；纽带；接合剂；牙骨质；补牙物；基石 vt.用水泥涂；巩固 vi.接合起来', '1. The sack of cement hit the ground with a thump. 水泥袋砰的一声落在地上。 2. Custom was in early days the cement of society. 习俗是早期社会维系的纽带。 3. The floor has been cemented over. 地板上铺了一层水泥。 4. They decided to cement the pavement. 他们决定在人行道上铺上水泥。 5. Snow is cementing. 雪正在凝结。', '名词: cementer 过去式: cemented 过去分词: cemented 现在分词: cementing 第三人称单数: cements');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pail', '[peɪl]', 'n.桶；一桶之量', '1. She poured some water into the pail. 她把一些水倒进提桶里。 2. The sway of the pail cause some milk to spill out. 桶的摇晃使一些牛奶溢了出来。 3. I want a pail of milk. 我想要一桶牛奶。 4. He lifted a pail of water from the ground. 他把一桶水从地上提了起来。', '名词: pailful');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('illusion', '[ɪ\'luːʒn]', 'n.错觉；幻觉；错误的信仰(或观念)', '1. Mirrors in a room often give an illusion of space. 房间里的镜子常给人一种空间增大的错觉。 2. A mirage is an optical illusion. 海市蜃楼是一种视错觉。 3. I thought I saw a ghost but it was just an optical illusion. 我以为我看见鬼了，其实只是一种幻觉。 4. This creates an illusion of variety. 这造成了一种多样化的幻觉。', '形容词: illusional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nephew', '[\'nefjuː]', 'n.外甥；侄子', '1. My little nephew is very naughty. 我的外甥特别调皮。 2. He decided to take his nephew abroad. 他决定把他的外甥带出国。 3. To my surprise, I found my nephew dressed in a girl\'s skirt. 令我惊奇的是，我侄子穿着女孩的裙子。 4. His nephew is an uncouth young man. 他的侄子是一个粗野的年轻人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rebel', '[\'rebl]', 'n.反叛者；造反者；叛逆者 v.造反；反抗；反感', '1. The rebels made regular attacks on the railways. 叛军不时地袭击铁路。 2. The rebel wanted to get away from the country. 造反者想脱离国家。 3. The woman was a rebel against feudal ethics. 那个女人是封建礼教的叛逆。 4. I\'ve always been the rebel of the family. 我在家里向来是个叛逆者。 5. When a lot of people rebel, there is a rebellion. 当许多人造反时，就出现了起义。', '过去式: rebelled 过去分词: rebelled 现在分词: rebelling 第三人称单数: rebels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comprehension', '[ˌkɑːmprɪ\'henʃn]', 'n.理解；理解力；领悟能力', '1. It is above comprehension. 那是难于理解的。 2. This event was a tragedy that strained all comprehension. 这一事件是人们怎么也不能理解的一个悲剧。 3. It\'s quite past my comprehension. 这件事已远超出我的理解力了。 4. Learning Chinese, you must have good comprehension. 学习汉语,必须要有很强的理解力', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('machinery', '[mə\'ʃiːnəri]', 'n.机械；(总称)机器', '1. We use tractors to pull farm machinery. 我们使用拖拉机牵引农业机械。 2. There was a ceaseless noise of machinery. 机器不停地发出噪音。 3. Some of the machinery is still standing idle. 有些机械仍然闲置着。 4. There was very little outlay on new machinery. 添置新机器的开支微乎其微。', '名词复数: machineries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blunt', '[blʌnt]', 'adj.钝的；迟钝的；直率的 v.使迟钝；变钝', '1. Blunt scissors don\'t cut cleanly. 钝剪刀剪不齐。 2. My pencil is blunt, could you lend me a knife to sharpen it? 我的铅笔钝了，你能借我把刀子削一削吗？ 3. It involves systematic yet banal design, and blunt reportage. 它使用系统的，然而平庸的设计和迟钝的新闻报道。 4. He\'s very blunt and will tell you what he thinks about anything. 他的个性非常直率,会把他所想的都说出来。 5. His mind was blunted by boredom. 他的头脑因厌烦而变得迟钝。', '副词: bluntly 比较级: blunter 最高级: bluntest 名词: bluntness 过去式: blunted 过去分词: blunted 现在分词: blunting 第三人称单数: blunts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pave', '[peɪv]', 'vt.铺路；铺设；铺满；安排', '1. The road was paved with cobblestones. 那条路是用鹅卵石铺成的。 2. The town council decided to pave the square before the Hall. 市议会决定在市政厅前铺一个广 3. The bricks are to pave the courtyard. 这些砖要用来铺院子。 4. Our garden is well paved with flowers. 我们的园子里鲜花遍地。', '名词: paver 过去式: paved 过去分词: paved 现在分词: paving 第三人称单数: paves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ethnic', '[\'eθnɪk]', 'adj.种族的；民族的；有民族特色的 n.少数民族的一员', '1. Canada is a multicultural country. Regardless of your ethnic origin, you will feel at home in Canada; 加拿大是一个多元文化国家,无论你为何种族,在加拿大你都会感到安适; 2. Along the way, tourists can see the Tujia ethnic minorities tilling the land. 沿着这条路,旅游者可以看到土家族的人在耕地。 3. That\'s why you can find almost every kind of ethnic food in America. 那也就是为什么在美国你几乎可以看到所有不同民族的食物。 4. Now all the 55 ethnic minorities have their own college students,and some even are master\'s and doctor\'s degree holders. 目前，55个少数民族都有了本民族的大学生，有的还有了硕士生和博士生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('priority', '[praɪ\'ɔːrəti]', 'n.优先权；优先；优先顺序', '1. This is the key and should be given top priority. 这是关键，要放在第一位。 2. Efficiency does not always have priority. 效率不一定总是优先。 3. Improving the plight of teachers is indeed a priority item. 改善教师的困难处境的确是优先处理的一件事情。', '名词复数: priorities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('industry', '[\'ɪndəstri]', 'n.工业；产业；行业；勤勉；勤劳', '1. Since the advent of atomic power, there have been great changes in industry. 自从原子动力问世以后，工业发生了巨大的变化。 2. The tourist trade has become a real industry. 旅游业已经成为真正的产业。 3. The information industry is an infant industry in our country. 信息产业在我国是新兴产业。 4. He wants to widen his knowledge of the industry. 他想扩充自己在这一行业的知识。', '名词复数: industries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compass', '[\'kʌmpəs]', 'n.圆规；指南针；范围 vt.达到；围绕；图谋', '1. Now we begin to draw a circle with compasses. 现在我们开始用圆规画一个圆。 2. I need a compass to draw a circle. 我需要一支圆规画圆。 3. A compass needle points to the north. 罗盘的指针永远指向北方。 4. The compass was invented by the Chinese, as is well known. 众所周知,指南针是中国人发明的。 5. In order to compass our object we must work hard. 为了达到我们的目标，我们必须努力工作。', '形容词: compassable 过去式: compassed 过去分词: compassed 现在分词: compassing 第三人称单数: compasses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blush', '[blʌʃ]', 'n.脸红；羞愧 vi.泛红；羞愧', '1. Her blush witnessed her agitation. 她脸红表示了她的激动。 2. She turn away to hide her blush. 她扭过脸，怕人见她脸红。 3. That story might raise a blush on a young girl\'s cheeks . 那个故事可能使少女听了脸红。 4. I have to blush to admit that thing. 我不得不羞愧地承认了那件事。 5. She would blush at the drop of a hat. 她动不动就脸红。', '形容词: blushful 副词: blushingly 过去式: blushed 过去分词: blushed 现在分词: blushing 第三人称单数: blushes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('look', '[lʊk]', 'v.看；寻找；显得看起来；注视；面向 n.看；样子；脸色', '1. He looked at the baby with a smile. 他笑着看着这个婴儿。 2. They looked forward very much to seeing him again. 他们非常盼望再次见到他。 3. He turned on the torch to look for his keys. 他打开了手电筒，寻找钥匙。 4. He looks nervous. 他看上去很紧张。 5. Let\'s take a look round the exhibition. 咱们看看展览吧。', '过去式: looked 过去分词: looked 现在分词: looking 第三人称单数: looks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remove', '[rɪ\'muːv]', 'v.消除；脱掉；免除；搬迁', '1. He removed the mud from his shoes. 他去掉鞋上的泥。 2. How can we remove the husk of the grains? 我们怎样去掉谷物的外皮？ 3. Come and remove your wet coat. 过来把你的湿上衣脱掉。 4. She asked me to remove my shnes. 她让我把鞋脱掉。', '名词: remover 过去式: removed 过去分词: removed 现在分词: removing 第三人称单数: removes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('render', '[\'rendər]', 'vt.提供；表现；使成为；宣布；翻译；回报；给予补偿；【计】渲染 n.粉刷；打底；交纳', '1. We are going to render them economic assistance. 我们打算向他们提供经济援助。 2. The power of the ocean was beautifully rendered in the poem. 这首诗将大海的力量表现得非常完美。 3. His back injury had rendered him unfit for work. 他的背伤使他无法胜任这份工作。 4. The jury has rendered its verdict. 陪审团已经作出了裁决', '形容词: renderable 名词: renderer 过去式: rendered 过去分词: rendered 现在分词: rendering 第三人称单数: renders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('else', '[els]', 'adv.其他；此外；(常与or连用)否则、不然', '1. Ask somebody else. 问问别人。 2. Would you like anything else to drink? 你还要喝点别的什么吗? 3. Yesterday, we went to the department store and nowhere else. 昨天我们到百货公司去了, 其他什么地方也没去。 4. Hurry, or else you\'ll be late. 快点儿，不然你要迟到了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scold', '[skoʊld]', 'v.责骂；训斥 n.斥责；爱责骂的人', '1. Don\'t scold the child without reason. 不可无缘无故地责骂小孩。 2. You shouldn\'t scold him on the slightest pretence. 你不应该以一点点借口就责骂他。 3. I hate to scold, but you mustn\'t scatter your things all over the place. 我不想训斥你，但你总不该把东西到处乱丢。 4. The disobedient son went out of his way to scold his parents. 这个不孝顺的儿子越出常轨谴责父母。 5. His father gave him a bad scold this morning. 他父亲今晨狠狠训了他一顿。', '副词: scoldingly 名词: scolder 过去式: scolded 过去分词: scolded 现在分词: scolding 第三人称单数: scolds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spiritual', '[\'spɪrɪtʃuəl]', 'adj.精神的；心灵的；与上帝有关的 n.(尤指美国南部黑人的)圣歌', '1. Many young people could not resist the spiritual pollution. 很多年轻人不能抵制精神污染。 2. I care more about the spiritual life than the substantial life. 和物质生活相比，我更注重精神生活。 3. The monks were arraigned for not teaching things spiritual. 修道士们因不讲授有关心灵的道理而受到指责。', '副词: spiritually 名词: spiritualness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abroad', '[ə\'brɔːd]', 'adv.到国外；广为流传 adj.在国外；海外(一般作表语)', '1. He is travelling abroad. 他要到国外旅行。 2. He lived abroad for many years. 他在国外居住了许多年。 3. The news spread abroad. 那消息四处传播。 4. There\'s a rumour abroad that she intends to leave the company. 谣言盛传她打算离开公司。 5. Our products have entered the markets abroad. 我们的产品已打入国外市场。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('besides', '[bɪ\'saɪdz]', 'prep.除 ... 之外 adv.此外；也', '1. No one writes to me besides you. 除你以外，没有人给我写信。 2. There will be five of us for dinner, besides John. 除约翰外，还有我们五个人要一起吃饭。 3. He has been to Mexico but nowhere besides. 他曾去过墨西哥但没去过别的地方。 4. He gave me a book,a pen and some money besides. 他给我一本书，一支钢笔，此外还给一些钱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('worthwhile', '[ˌwɜːrθ\'waɪl]', 'adj.值得(做)的', '1. Thank you for making my visit so worthwhile. I shall treasure your friendship and kind hospitality you have given me. 感谢你们使我的访问如此有价值。我将珍惜我们之间的友谊及你们给予我的盛情款待。 2. That\'s worthwhile. 那是值得的。', '名词: worthwhileness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kit', '[kɪt]', 'n.成套工具；工具箱；装备 vt.装备', '1. The plumber lost his kit on the way home. 这位水管工人在回家的路上把工具丢了。 2. There is a repair kit provided in the boot of each car. 每辆车的行李箱内都备有工具箱。 3. They marched twenty miles in full kit. 他们带着全副装备行军二十英里。 4. Kit this man out with everything he needs. 他需要什麽就给他什麽装备。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('secondary', '[\'sekənderi]', 'adj.次要的；从属的；中等教育的 n.副手；次要位置', '1. It\'s a question of secondary importance. 这是个次要的问题。 2. All other considerations are secondary to his safety. 现在首先要考虑的是他的安全，其他事都是次要的。 3. We should control the secondary pollution. 我们应该控制二次污染。 4. The disease is usually due to secondary infection. 这个病是继发性感染引起的。 5. They put the growth of worker salary in secondary. 他们把工人的薪水增长放在次要位置。', '副词: secondarily 名词: secondariness 名词复数: secondaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preference', '[\'prefrəns]', 'n.偏爱；优先；喜爱物；优惠', '1. She has a preference for blue. 她特别喜欢蓝色。 2. It\'s entirely a matter of preference. 这完全是个见仁见智的问题。 3. A polar bear has a preference for cold weather. 北极熊喜欢寒冷的天气。 4. While selecting job applicants, we usually give preference to those with some experience. 在筛选求职者的过程中,我们通常优先考虑有一定经验的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sad', '[sæd]', 'adj.悲哀的；忧愁的；伤心的', '1. Her eyes moisten as she listen to the sad story. 听著这悲伤的故事,她的眼睛湿润了。 2. My heart broke at the sad news. 知道这悲伤的消息时 3. Here we had, not long ago, a very sad funeral in this church. 不久以前,这教会举行了一次悲哀的丧礼。 4. What deserves being thoughtful and sad when you are just a child? 小小年纪,有什么值得你心事重重,满腹忧愁?', '副词: sadly 比较级: sadder 最高级: saddest 名词: sadness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('our', '[\'aʊər]', 'adj.我们的', '1. He enrolled our names. 他把我们的名字登记下来了。 2. That\'s not our business. 那事与我们不相干。 3. Our partnership dates back to (ie We have been partners since) 1960. 我们从1960年就合伙了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('precious', '[\'preʃəs]', 'adj.宝贵的；珍贵的；矫揉造作的 adv.极其 n.<口>宝贝，心爱的人', '1. You should make good use of every precious minute to study. 你应很好利用宝贵的每一分钟去学习。 2. Pandas are precious creatures. 熊猫是珍贵的动物。 3. That old book is my most precious possession. 那本旧书是我最珍贵的财产。 4. He is a rather precious young man. 他是一个惺惺作态的年轻男子。 5. Precious few people can afford prices like that. 没有什麽人出得起那个价钱。', '副词: preciously 名词: preciousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('desperate', '[\'despərət]', 'adj.绝望的；不顾一切的；极其想要的', '1. The situation is desperate. 情况令人感到绝。 2. I had no money left and was desperate. 我一点钱都没有了,简直绝望了。 3. They made a desperate plea for help. 他们不顾一切地恳求帮助。 4. His failure made him desperate. 他因失败而铤而走险。', '副词: desperately 名词: desperateness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('laundry', '[\'lɔːndri]', 'n.洗衣店；洗衣；要洗的衣服', '1. Send these clothed over to the laundry. 把这些衣服送到洗衣店去洗。 2. This laundry makes deliveries on Thursday. 这个洗衣店星期四送衣服。 3. I\'d like to have laundry service. 我需要洗衣服务。 4. Why don\'t you help your mother do the laundry? 你为什么不帮你妈妈洗衣服?', '名词复数: laundries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('affiliate', '[ə\'fɪlieɪt]', 'n.分公司；附属机构 vt.使隶属于；接纳；追溯 vi.发生联系', '1. It is an affiliate of the Red Cross. 它是红十字会的一个份子。 2. Do I get the product as part of the affiliate program? 我得到的附属产品作为节目? 3. I affiliate myself with their team to get more information on the share market. 我和他们组密切联系以获得更多股票市场的信息。 4. The Committee regrets that it cannot right now affiliate your group to their Society. 那个委员会很抱歉，不能马上将你们的团体并入他们的学会。 5. If we affiliate, we will have a better chance to win. 如果我们加入的话，赢的可能性更大。', '名词: affiliation 过去式: affiliated 过去分词: affiliated 现在分词: affiliating 第三人称单数: affiliates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('open', '[\'oʊpən]', 'adj.开着的；开放的；公开的 v.打开；张开；展开；摊开；开始(某事物)；开张；营业；以…开头；宣布启用 n.户外；公开', '1. The fresh air blew in from the open window. 新鲜空气从开着的窗户吹进来。 2. One day, I came home to find my garage open. 有一天，我到家时发现车库的门是开着的。 3. She has fall asleep with an open book in her lap. 她睡着了,腿上还摊开着一本书。 4. I\'m so sleepy that I can hardly keep my eyes open. 我睡意太浓，眼睛都快睁不开了。 5. Can you open the bottle with the opener? 你能用启子将瓶子打开吗？ 6. In the summer, we camped in the open . 夏天我们在户外野营。', '副词: openly 名词: openness 过去式: opened 过去分词: opened 现在分词: opening 第三人称单数: opens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('batch', '[bætʃ]', 'n.一批；一炉；一次所制之量 v.分批处理', '1. The second batch of sugar is better than the first. 第二批制成的糖比第一批好。 2. There are a batch of tourists over there. 那里有一批旅游者。 3. The first batch of police-women went on duty in Jinan in 1959. 济南第-批女警察是1959年开始值勤。 4. These cakes were baked in batches of twenty. 这些蛋糕是以二十个为一炉烘烤的。', '过去式: batched 过去分词: batched 现在分词: batching 第三人称单数: batches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nightmare', '[\'naɪtˌmeə]', 'n.恶梦；使人极其痛苦的事情或经历；梦魇', '1. The nightmare gave her the creeps. 那场恶梦使她不寒而栗。 2. Will I wake up from this nightmare? 我会从这个恶梦中醒来吗? 3. The holocaust survivors have lived a nightmare. 大屠杀幸存者经历了一场噩梦。 4. Losing a child is most people\'s worst nightmare. 对于大多数人来说，丧子之痛是最可怕的梦魇。', '形容词: nightmarish 副词: nightmarishly 名词: nightmarishness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('location', '[loʊ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.位置；外景拍摄地；定位；地点', '1. The town is a good location for a young doctor. 这个小镇很适宜于一位青年医生安家。 2. He indicated the location of the Persian Gulf with a pen on the map. 他用一支笔在地图上标出了波斯湾的位置。 3. Most scenes of the film were shot on location. 影片的大部分镜头是在外景拍摄地拍的。 4. They switch the location of the movie to Hawaii. 他们把这部电影的外景拍摄地改为夏威夷。', '形容词: locational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overturn', '[ˌoʊvər\'tɜːrn]', 'v.翻倒；推翻；颠覆 n.倾覆；打翻', '1. The boat overturned but didn\'t sank. 小船翻了，但没有沉。 2. The revolutionist planned to overturn this puppet regime. 革命者计划推翻傀儡政府。 3. Some high-ranking officers plotted to overturn the government. 有几名高级军官策划推翻政府。 4. The 21st century will overturn many of our basic assumptions about economic life. 21世纪将会颠覆很多我们关于经济生活的基础假设。 5. This is one of the important reasons for overturn of ro-ro ships. 这是许多滚装船发生倾覆的重要原因之一。', '过去式: overturned 过去分词: overturned 现在分词: overturning 第三人称单数: overturns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('real', '[\'riːəl]', 'adj.真实的；真的；正宗的；真正的；名副其实的；实际的；现实的；不动产的 adv.非常 n.真实；雷阿尔（昔日西班牙等地的货币）', '1. Children believe that these characters are real. 孩子们相信这些人物是真实的。 2. His face was drawn but the curtains were real. 他的脸是画的,但窗帘是真的。 3. You will try some real Chinese cuisine this time. 这次您将品尝正宗的中国菜。 4. She never had any real friends at school. 在学校，她从来没有交过真正的朋友。 5. I\'m not real familiar with the area 我不大熟悉这一带。 6. The real in us is silent; the acquired is talkative. 真实的自我沉默不语，后天的自我却喋喋不休。', '名词: realness 名词复数: reals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fortune', '[\'fɔːrtʃən]', 'n.命运；财产；运气', '1. Everyone is the architect of his own fortune. 每个人都是自己命运的创造者。 2. An ill marriage is a spring of ill fortune. 不良的婚姻是恶运的来源。 3. He dreamed of making a fortune. 他梦想发大财。 4. I rate his fortune at$10,000. 我估计他有1万美元的财产。', '过去式: fortuned 过去分词: fortuned 现在分词: fortuning 第三人称单数: fortunes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plead', '[pliːd]', 'v.辩护；恳求；提出借口；认罪', '1. You should get a lawyer to plead for your case. 你该请一位律师为你的案子辩护。 2. I heard him plead in court only once. 我只有一次听到他在法庭上作辩护。 3. With that kind of man you will plead in vain. 你恳求那种人将是白费力气。 4. He would see her and plead his cause again in person. 他要去见她，当面再度恳求。', '形容词: pleadable 副词: pleadingly 名词: pleader 过去式: pleaded/pled 过去分词: pleaded/pled 现在分词: pleading 第三人称单数: pleads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('speed', '[spiːd]', 'n.速度；迅速 v.加速；急行', '1. The police are advising motorists to reduce speed because of the fog. 由于有雾，警察告诫驾车者减慢速度。 2. This plane can reach speeds in excess of 1000 kilometers an hour. 这架飞机可以达到每小时一千公里以上的速度。 3. She finished typewriting the letter at speed. 她迅速打好那封信。 4. All this must be done at very great speed. 这一切都需要非常迅速地干完。 5. The train soon speeded up. 火车不久就加快了速度。', '过去式: sped/speeded 过去分词: sped/speeded 现在分词: speeding 第三人称单数: speeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('magistrate', '[\'mædʒɪstreɪt]', 'n.地方法官；行政官', '1. The thief was brought before the magistrate. 窃贼被带到地方法官前受审。 2. The magistrate remanded him in custody for two weeks. 法官命令把他拘留两星期。 3. The President is the chief magistrate of the United States. 总统是美国的最高行政官。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stone', '[stoʊn]', 'n.【U】石料 n.【C】石头；宝石；(水果的)硬核 n.英石(重量单位；合14磅) vt.向 ... 扔石头；去掉(水果的)核', '1. The brick house was faced with stone. 这座砖房石料贴面。 2. The inscription on the stone had worn away. 刻在石头上的文字已磨损了。 3. The beetle scurried away when I lifted the stone. 我把石头搬起来时，那只甲虫跑了。 4. A diamond ring with five stones is quite expensive. 镶有五颗宝石的钻戒十分昂贵。 5. A mob stoned and robbed the shops. 一群暴民用石头砸了商店，并抢劫店里的货物。', '名词: stoner 过去式: stoned 过去分词: stoned 现在分词: stoning 第三人称单数: stones');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('again', '[ə\'ɡen]', 'adv.再；又', '1. Try again. 再试试。 2. Say that again, please. 请再说一遍。 3. I am longing to see my friend Jack again. 我渴望再见到我的朋友杰克。 4. I am sorry-she\'s out. Can you ring again later? 对不起－她出去了。你过些时候再打电话来好吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shape', '[ʃeɪp]', 'n.形状；形式；身材；定形 vt.塑造；定形；使 ... 成形', '1. This island is triangular in shape. 这个岛的外形呈三角形。 2. I\'m having trouble giving shape to my ideas in this essay. 我在这篇文章中表达不清自己的想法。 3. John: Well, I\'m a bit out of shape and I was thinking of joining your gym. 嗯,我身材有点走样,正考虑加入你们的健身俱乐部。 4. In the process it became less amorphous in shape. 在过程中它变得较不无定形在形状。 5. It was the Greeks who shaped the thinking of Western man. 正是希腊人影响了西方人的思维。', '形容词: shapable 名词: shaper 过去式: shaped 过去分词: shaped 现在分词: shaping 第三人称单数: shapes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clerk', '[klɜːrk]', 'n.职员；办事员 vi.(作为职员)工作', '1. The bank clerk peered at the customer through/from behind the grille. 银行的职员从格栅後面看著顾客。 2. The bank manager was really to blame, though he tried to pin it on a clerk. 真正受责备的应该是银行经理，可是他却想把责任推到一个职员身上。 3. She is the filing clerk of our company. 她是我们公司的档案员。 4. The clerk marked up his daybook before going home. 办事员在回家前记好当天的日记帐。 5. She clerks in a store(bank). 她在商店（银行）当售货员（职员）。', '名词: clerkdom 过去式: clerked 过去分词: clerked 现在分词: clerking 第三人称单数: clerks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resource', '[\'riːsɔːrs]', 'n.资源；机敏；才略；寄托；消遣', '1. If I may refer back to the problem we discussed, I think we shall stress on the conservation of our natural resource. 请允许我重提我们刚才讨论过的问题，我想我们应该强调保存我们的自然资源。 2. Resources management is an important business skill. 资源管理是一项重要的经营技能。 3. He is a man of great resource. 他是一个足智多谋的人。 4. The job called for all my resources of energy and patience. 这项工作需要我拿出自己的全部精力和耐性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scientist', '[\'saɪəntɪst]', 'n.科学家', '1. The young girl aspired to be a scientist. 小女孩立志要做一名科学家。 2. When will scientist conquer cancer? 科学家什么时候才能征服癌症呢？ 3. The scientist needs some delicate instruments. 这位科学家需要一些精密的仪器。 4. The scientist is distinguished in many spheres of knowledge. 这位科学家在许多知识领域中都是杰出的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sniff', '[snɪf]', 'vi.嗅；嗤之以鼻；找出 vt.嗅到；吸入；嗤之以鼻地说 n.嗅；吸气；气味', '1. The dog was sniffing at the lamppost. 那条狗在街灯柱旁嗅来嗅去。 2. They are training these dogs to sniff out drugs. 他们训练狗嗅出毒品来。 3. His generous offer is not to be sniffed at. 对他的慷慨厚意不可嗤之以鼻。 4. We shouldn\'t sniff at this opportunity--we any not get another like it. 我们不可小看这个机会--也许我们再也找不到这样的机会了。 5. Doves and wolves love to sniff puff enough to cough and sneeze. 鸽子和野狼喜欢嗅粉扑，嗅到咳嗽，打喷嚏。 6. They are training these dogs to sniff out drugs. 他们训练狗嗅出毒品来。', '形容词: sniffable 名词: sniffer 过去式: sniffed 过去分词: sniffed 现在分词: sniffing 第三人称单数: sniffs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('census', '[\'sensəs]', 'n.人口普查；户口普查；统计', '1. The census is taken one time every four years in our country. 我国每四年一次人口普查。 2. The census revealed a declining birth rate. 人口普查结果表明出生率在下降。 3. This census is an invaluable resource for tracing family history. 人口普查是追查家族史的一种宝贵资源。 4. In the United States there is a census every ten years. 在美国每十年做一次户囗调查。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('halt', '[hɔːlt]', 'n.停止；止步 v.停止；中止；暂停 v.踌躇；犹豫；跛行', '1. He tried to bring that debate to a halt. 他试图使这场辩论停止。 2. The officer called a halt to attacks. 那个军官下令停止进攻。 3. The thought brought her to an abrupt halt. 她一想到这个便猛地停下了。 4. No one can halt the advance of history. 谁也阻挡不了历史的前进。 5. He never halts in his speech. 他说话从不吞吞吐吐。', '过去式: halted 过去分词: halted 现在分词: halting 第三人称单数: halts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('definite', '[\'defɪnət]', 'adj.明确的；一定的；有把握的', '1. His vague ideas crystallized into a definite plan. 他那些模糊的想法变成了一个明确的计划。 2. The workers demand a definite answer. 工人们要求一个明确的答复。 3. You have our definite support. 我们绝对支持您。 4. It\'s definite that he will win. 他肯定会赢。', '副词: definitely 名词: definiteness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('umbrella', '[ʌm\'brelə]', 'n.伞；雨伞；庇护', '1. The wind blew my umbrella inside out. 风把我的伞吹得翻过去了。 2. You should take an umbrella just as a precaution. 你该带把伞，有备无患。 3. Can you identify your umbrella among this lot? 你能在这些伞中认出你自己的伞吗？ 4. She was holding up an umbrella. 她打着雨伞。', '形容词: umbrellaless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stiff', '[stɪf]', 'adj.硬的；僵直的；艰难的；生硬的；拘谨的；烈性的 adv.极其；僵硬地 n.死尸；流浪汉；过于拘谨的人；吝啬鬼；醉鬼', '1. Shoes are often stiff when they are new. 新鞋刚穿起来常常都是硬邦邦的。 2. She cleaned the sink with a stiff brush. 她用硬毛刷清洗水槽。 3. His legs felt stiff from having sat for so long. 由于坐得太久，他的双腿感到僵直。 4. He has to take a stiff test before he is qualified. 在取得资格之前,他必须通过一次艰难的考试。 5. The opera bored me stiff. 这个歌剧真把我腻烦透了。', '形容词: stiffish 副词: stiffly 比较级: stiffer 最高级: stiffest 名词: stiffness 过去式: stiffed 过去分词: stiffed 现在分词: stiffing 第三人称单数: stiffs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('auto', '[\'ɔːtoʊ]', 'n.汽车 pref.自动的 v.乘汽车', '1. He made the best time in the auto race. 他的汽车赛中开得最快。 2. The auto industry has brought many people to Detroit. 汽车工业把许多人吸引到了底特律。 3. That auto company is coming out with several new models. 那家汽车公司将把好几种新型号产品投入市场。 4. The Detroit auto workers went out for higher pay. 底特律的汽车工人为争取提高工资而罢工。', '名词复数: autos 过去式: autoed 过去分词: autoed 现在分词: autoing 第三人称单数: autos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('characteristic', '[ˌkærəktə\'rɪstɪk]', 'n.特点；特性；特色 adj.典型的；特有的', '1. Ambition is a characteristic of all successful businessmen. 雄心勃勃是所有成功生意人的共同特点。 2. Kindness is one of his characteristics. 和善是他的特性之一。 3. A characteristic of the camel is its ability to live for a long time without water. 骆驼的特点是不喝水也能活很长时间。 4. They have been affected by trends in Italy too much to keep their own characteristics. 他们受意大利潮流的影响太大了,以致无法保持自己的特色。 5. It is the characteristic attitude of people towards life in those post-war years. 这是战后人们典型的处世态度。', '副词: characteristically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('campus', '[\'kæmpəs]', 'n.校园；场地 adj.校园的', '1. The new library was built in the centre of the campus. 新图书馆建在校园的中心。 2. There are many people taking pictures on campus. 好多人在校园里拍照。 3. The campus life is very wonderful. 校园生活多姿多彩。', '名词复数: campuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('create', '[kri\'eɪt]', 'v.创造；造成 adj.<古>创造的', '1. Some people believe that God created the world. 有些人相信上帝创造了世界。 2. An artist should create beautiful things. 一个艺术家应该创造美丽的东西。 3. This is the kind of atmosphere we want to create. 我们就想造成这种氛围。 4. That can create a vicious circle. 这会造成恶性循环。', '过去式: created 过去分词: created 现在分词: creating 第三人称单数: creates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('good', '[ɡʊd]', 'adj.好的；上等的；优秀的 n.好处；善行 (复)goods：商品；货物.', '1. A good video camera will cost you a lot of money. 一台好的摄像机要花掉你很多钱。 2. My one good suit is at the cleaner\'s. 我那套讲究的衣服还在洗衣店里呢。 3. If you train hard, you\'ll make a good footballer. 你要刻苦训练就能成为优秀的足球运动员。 4. Complaining won\'t do you any good. 抱怨对你没有任何好处。', '比较级: better 最高级: best');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tropical', '[\'trɑːpɪkl]', 'adj.热带的；炎热的；热带植物的', '1. Her motherland is in the tropical region. 她的祖国位于热带地区。 2. These tropical flowers have bright colors. 这些热带花卉颜色很艳丽。 3. He is used to the tropical weather. 他习惯了炎热的天气。 4. Summer was almost tropical last year. 去年的夏天十分炎热。', '副词: tropically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glad', '[ɡlæd]', 'adj.高兴的；乐意的 v.<古>使高兴 n.剑兰', '1. I\'m glad to hear he\'s feeling better. 听说他身体好些了，我很高兴。 2. I am glad we have come together at last. 很高兴我们终于取得了一致。 3. I\'d be glad to lend you the money. 我很乐意借给你钱。 4. If you\'d like me to help you, I\'d be only too glad to. 若要我帮忙，我十分乐意相助。', '副词: gladly 比较级: gladder 最高级: gladdest 名词: gladness 过去式: gladded 过去分词: gladded 现在分词: gladding 第三人称单数: glads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('insult', '[ɪn\'sʌlt]', 'n.侮辱；辱骂；冒犯 vt.侮辱；辱骂；凌辱', '1. He made a witty comeback to the insult. 他对别人的侮辱给予一个机智的反驳。 2. She reacted to the insult by turning her back on him. 她受辱之后就不再理睬他了。 3. He shouted insults at the boy who had kicked him. 他大声辱骂那个踢了他的男孩。 4. He felt deeply insulted by her rude words. 她无礼的言词使他深感受辱。', '副词: insultingly 名词: insulter 过去式: insulted 过去分词: insulted 现在分词: insulting 第三人称单数: insults');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feather', '[\'feðər]', 'n.羽毛；翎毛；种类 vt.用羽毛装饰 vi.长出羽毛', '1. Feather is very light, so that we say \"as light as a feather\". 羽毛很轻，因此我们说“轻如鸿毛”。 2. A feather floated down on the wind. 一根羽毛随风飘落。 3. The peacock displayed its fine tail feather. 那只孔雀展现其美丽的尾部羽毛。 4. Birds of a feather flock together. 物以类聚，人以群分 5. The chick will soon feather out. 这只小鸡很快就要长羽毛了。', '过去式: feathered 过去分词: feathered 现在分词: feathering 第三人称单数: feathers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('festival', '[\'festɪvl]', 'adj.节日的；喜庆的 n.节日；欢宴；庆祝及祭祀', '1. We all wore festival costumes to the ball. 我们都穿著节日的盛装去参加舞会。 2. The carnival was immersed in a festival atmosphere. 嘉年华沉浸在节日的气氛中。 3. We all immersed in the gaiety of the Spring Festival. 我们都沉浸在春节的欢乐之中。 4. The Nadam Festival is a traditional occasion for Mongols to get together for a few days of festivity. 传统地，蒙古国人民在那达慕节要聚集欢宴几天。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('negligible', '[\'neɡlɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.可以忽略的；微不足道的', '1. The damage to my car is negligible. 我的汽车的损坏是极轻微的。 2. The rumors and slanders is negligible to me. 流言蜚语对于我来说是可以忽略的。 3. Details are negligible as far as I know. 我认为这些细节完全可以忽略。 4. The risks were represented as negligible. 把这么冒险的事说得微不足道。', '副词: negligibly 名词: negligibility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('colonial', '[kə\'loʊniəl]', 'adj.殖民地的 n.殖民地居民', '1. France was once a colonial power. 法国一度是占有殖民地的强国。 2. American Independence War is really a colonial war. 美国的独立战争实际是一场关于殖民地的战争。 3. His forefathers were colonial in the control of England. 他祖先是英国殖民地居民。', '副词: colonially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drum', '[drʌm]', 'n.鼓；鼓状物；鼓声 vi.击鼓；连续敲击；引起兴趣 vt.灌输；击鼓；逐出', '1. The beats of the drum were steady and slow. 鼓声平稳而缓慢。 2. The oil flowed over the rim of the drum. 油从汽油桶的边缘流出。 3. The drum on the battlefield stimulated the soldiers to fight more bravely. 战场上的鼓声鼓舞了战士们,使他们更加英勇的作战。 4. People in the village drummed for my being enrolled by Peking University. 村子里的人为我顺利地考取北京大学而击鼓欢庆。 5. She drummed it into the children that they can\'t cross the road alone. 她反复地给孩子们说,他们不可以独自横过马路。', '过去式: drummed 过去分词: drummed 现在分词: drumming 第三人称单数: drums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('liable', '[\'laɪəbl]', 'adj.有义务的；应负责的；有 ... 倾向；可能的；易遭受…的，易患…（病）的', '1. He declared that he was not liable for his wife\'s debts. 他宣称对妻子的债务不负责。 2. Parents are liable forchildren\'s education. 父母应负责孩子的教育。 3. They are liable to run off with your money. 他们有卷款而走的倾向。 4. We are liable to make mistakes. 我们都易犯错误。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bucket', '[\'bʌkɪt]', 'n.【C】水桶；（机器上的）桶装物；大量 vi.颠簸行进；下倾盆大雨 vt.装在桶里', '1. Go and fill this bucket with water for me. 去替我装满一桶水来。 2. He came down the hill carrying a bucket of water. 他提著一桶水下山来了。 3. I knocked over the bucket and the water poured (out) all over the floor. 我打翻了水桶，水流了一地。 4. They buy tickets by the bucket and sell them at a profit. 他们买了很多票,并且再卖掉以获取利润。 5. The old car bucketed along at about thirty. 那辆旧车以30公里左右的时速行驶。 6. The girl was bucketing water from the well. 那姑娘在用桶从井里打水。', '过去式: bucketed 过去分词: bucketed 现在分词: bucketing 第三人称单数: buckets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overhead', '[ˌoʊvər\'hed]', 'n.经常开支；普通用费 adj.高架的；在头上的 adv.在头顶上；在空中；在高处 [计算机] 总开销.', '1. Their office is in central Beijing, so their overhead is very high. 他们的办事处设在北京市中心，所以他们的日常开支很大。 2. The overhead costs are ridiculously expensive. 日常开支太高了。 3. This button turns on your overhead light. 这个按钮用来开亮您头顶上方的灯。 4. The hawk is hovering overhead. 鹰在头顶上盘旋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('doctorate', '[\'dɑːktərət]', 'n.博士学位', '1. He earned his doctorate in philosophy. 他获得了哲学博士学位。 2. A doctorate can take four to six years. 博士学位需要四到六年。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('critical', '[\'krɪtɪkl]', 'adj.批评的；挑剔的；决定性的；危险的 adj.临界的', '1. It is difficult enough to be critical of our own mistakes. 对我们自己的错误采取批评的态度确实非常困难。 2. She viewed the findings with a critical eye. 她以批评的眼光看待这些研究结果。 3. Our clients are very critical on quality. 我们的客户对商品的质量是很挑剔的。 4. Joint strategic maneuver is critical. 联合战略行动是决定性的。 5. These materials become quite soft and flexible above critical temperature. 这些材料在临界温度以上变得十分柔软和易于弯曲。', '副词: critically 名词: criticalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gallop', '[\'ɡæləp]', 'n.疾驰；飞奔 v.飞驰；急速进行', '1. The horse went off at a gallop across the field. 那匹马疾驰起来跑过田野。 2. All the horses broke into a gallop. 所有的马突然飞奔起来。 3. The donkey began to trot faster , then to gallop. 驴开始跑得快起来了，然后飞奔。 4. Two people gallop whip and spur, do not come in the city a little while. 两人快马加鞭飞驰，不一会儿就来到城里。', '名词: galloper 过去式: galloped 过去分词: galloped 现在分词: galloping 第三人称单数: gallops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('norm', '[nɔːrm]', 'n.规范；标准', '1. Criminal behaviour seem to be the norm in this neighbourhood. 犯罪行为似乎是这一带的正常现象。 2. Law is a social norm reflecting the will of a state. 法是具有国家意志的社会规范。 3. You must adapt to the norms of the society you live in. 在社会中生活就要遵循社会行为准则。 4. There\'s a production norm below which each worker must not fall. 每个工人的产量都不得低于生产指标。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gut', '[ɡʌt]', 'n.内脏；肠子；羊肠线；胆量；勇气 vt.取出内脏；摧毁（内部） adj.本能的；（问题等）根本的', '1. Do not break the ink bag and cut the gut off. 除去内脏,小心别将墨袋刺穿。 2. It takes several hours for food to pass through the gut. 食物经过肠子需要几个小时。 3. The fishing line is made of gut. 钓鱼线是羊肠线做的。 4. He is a man with plenty of guts. 他是个很有魄力的人。 5. Gut the rabbit before you cook it. 烧煮之前先把兔子的内脏取出。 6. My immediate gut feeling was to refuse. 我本能的直接反应是拒绝。', '形容词: gutty 过去式: gutted 过去分词: gutted 现在分词: gutting 第三人称单数: guts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('institution', '[ˌɪnstɪ\'tuːʃn]', 'n.制定；制度；机构；名流', '1. The institution of school rules is necessary. 制定学校规则的是很有必要的。 2. Marriage is an institution in most societies. 婚姻是大多数社会早已确立的制度。 3. Marriage is love. Love is blind. Therefore marriage is an institution for the blind. 婚姻就是爱情,爱情是盲目的,所以婚姻是一所收容盲人的机构。 4. My uncle has become quite an institution at the club. 我叔叔在俱乐部里已是颇有名气的人物了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elsewhere', '[ˌels\'wer]', 'adv.别处', '1. I shall go elsewhere. 我要到别处去。 2. You can\'t find anything like this elsewhere. 像这样的东西你在别处找不到。 3. He lived elsewhere during the summer months. 他夏天住在别处。 4. If the restaurant is full we can go elsewhere. 如果餐馆客满了，我们得去别处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('endow', '[ɪn\'daʊ]', 'vt.捐助；赋予；使具有某种品质', '1. I can only endow 100 dollors at most. 我充其量只能捐助100美元。 2. He endowed the hospital with a large fortune. 他捐赠一笔巨款给这家医院。 3. She both built and endowed the hospital. 她不仅建了医院还给医院捐赠资金。 4. He is endowed with literary talent. 他有文学天分。', '过去式: endowed 过去分词: endowed 现在分词: endowing 第三人称单数: endows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shoot', '[ʃuːt]', 'v.发射；开枪；疾驰；拍照 n.发射；嫩枝 int.哇! 可恶! 哎呀!', '1. This is just a toy gun; it doesn\'t shoot. 这只是玩具枪, 不能发射子弹。 2. He shot the bird with his gun. 他用枪打鸟。 3. The sports car shot past us. 赛车从我们前面飞驰而过。 4. The scene was shot on location. 这个景是实地拍摄的。 5. The enemies made shoots at us. 敌人向我们发起射击。 6. Shoot! My coat is caught in the door. 哇，上衣被车门夹住了。', '名词: shooter 过去式: shot 过去分词: shot 现在分词: shooting 第三人称单数: shoots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stick', '[stɪk]', 'n.手杖；枝；杆 vt.刺入；插于；竖起 vi.钉住；坚持，遵守；粘贴；生效，起作用', '1. A walking stick is a must for me now. 如今我行走离不开手杖了。 2. We made the fire out of dry sticks. 我们用干柴枝来生火。 3. Hold the stick against crosswind. 向侧风方向压住杆。 4. A pin stuck me in the hand. 一根针刺入我的手。 5. Please help me to stick up the board on the big box. 请帮助我把木板钉在那个大木箱上。', '过去式: stuck 过去分词: stuck 现在分词: sticking 第三人称单数: sticks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('frequent', '[\'friːkwənt]', 'adj.频繁的；经常的 vt.常到；常去', '1. My girlfriend writes frequent letters to me. 我的女朋友频繁地给我写信。 2. Traffic accidents are alarmingly frequent of late. 近来交通事故频繁得吓人。 3. He is a frequent visitor to our house. 他是我们家的常客。 4. He suffers from frequent bouts of depression. 他患多发性抑郁症。 5. He used to frequent the town\'s bars and night-clubs. 他从前常去镇上的酒吧和夜总会。', '名词: frequentation 过去式: frequented 过去分词: frequented 现在分词: frequenting 第三人称单数: frequents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('specification', '[ˌspesɪfɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.规格；详述', '1. Can you give me a price list with specification? 你能否给我一份有规格说明的价目单吗？ 2. In case of need we can offer you some other brand of the same specification. 万一有需要,我们可供应同样规格的其它品牌货品。 3. I want to know his specification of details. 我想知道他对细节的详述。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('atom', '[\'ætəm]', 'n.原子；微粒', '1. Scientists have unlocked the secret of the atom. 科学家已经揭开了原子的秘密。 2. A molecule of water consists of two atoms of hydrogen and one atom of oxygen. 水分子含有两个氢原子和一个氧原子。 3. The atom bomb is the offspring of the 20th century physics. 原子弹是20世纪物理学的产物。 4. That cannot get up an atom of sympathy for them. 那并不能激发起人们对他们的丝毫同情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sugar', '[\'ʃʊɡər]', 'n.糖，食糖；糖缸；甜言蜜语，阿谀奉承；宝贝，心肝 v.使甜；在...上撒糖', '1. I bought him a packet of sugar. 我给他买了一袋糖果。 2. He put some sugar into his coffee. 他往咖啡里加了些糖。 3. If the lemonade tastes bitter,sugar it. 如果柠檬水发苦，就加糖。 4. Shall I sugar the milk for you? 我给你的牛奶加糖吗?', '名词: sugarer 过去式: sugared 过去分词: sugared 现在分词: sugaring 第三人称单数: sugars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fill', '[fɪl]', 'vt.装满；弥漫；填充；担任 n.足量', '1. Please fill the cup with water. 请把这个杯子装满水。 2. Smoke filled the room. 屋里尽是烟。 3. Life just gives you time and space, it\'s up to you to fill it. 生活只给我们时间和空间,我们自己决定如何去填充它。 4. He is competent enough to fill that position. 他完全胜任那个职位。 5. No more tea,thank you,I\'ve had my fill. 谢谢你,不要再添茶了,我已经喝足了。', '过去式: filled 过去分词: filled 现在分词: filling 第三人称单数: fills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('revelation', '[ˌrevə\'leɪʃn]', 'n.揭露；泄露；发觉；启示', '1. The revelation of his past lead to his resignation. 对他过去的揭露导致了他的辞职。 2. Have you read the ex-minister\'s amazing revelations in the newspaper? 你看了前任部长在报上揭露的那些惊人的事实没有？ 3. The revelation of the plot of the traitors caused their capture. 反叛者阴谋的泄露使他们被捕。 4. Her true nature was a revelation to me. 她的真实性格对我是一个新发现。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('parliament', '[\'pɑːrləmənt]', 'n.议会；国会；一届议会的会期', '1. Parliament will debate the nationalization issue next week. 议会将在下周辩论国有化议题。 2. He lost his seat in the Parliament at the election. 他在选举中失去了议会中的席位。 3. The Parliament decided to impeach the President. 国会决定弹劾总统。 4. Parliament has passed an Act forbidding the killing of rare animals. 国会通过了一项法令，禁止捕杀珍稀动物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('up', '[ʌp]', 'adv.向上；起来；上升；往上 prep.向上 adj.向上的；上行的 n.上升 v.上升；增加', '1. Put the packet up on the top shelf. 把这个包放到架子顶格上去。 2. I got up early this morning. 今天早晨我起床很早。 3. The import of cotton goods went up sharply in 1981. 一九八一年棉织品的进口量急遽上升。 4. The old man knocked the hoe handle up. 那位老人把锄头柄往上敲。 5. It is an up elevator. 这是向上运行的电梯。 6. The fuel prices are upping. 燃料价格在上升。', '过去式: upped 过去分词: upped 现在分词: upping 第三人称单数: ups');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scholarship', '[\'skɑːlərʃɪp]', 'n.奖学金；学问；学识', '1. The scholarship includes an allowance of 80 dollars for books. 奖学金包括八十美元的书籍费津贴。 2. He won a scholarship to Cambridge. 他获得一份到剑桥大学读书的奖学金。 3. She has been awarded a scholarship to study at Harvard. 她获得了去哈佛大学读书的奖学金。 4. I have not the gifts that are necessary for scholarship. 我没有做学问所必须的天资。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('black', '[blæk]', 'adj.黑的；不加牛奶的；很脏的；愤怒的；令人沮丧的；邪恶的；阴沉的；机密的；黑色幽默的 n.黑色；黑人；黑色物 v.抵制；(使)变黑', '1. Do you have a black jacket? 你有一件黑夹克吗？ 2. How do you like coffee, black or white ? 你喜欢什么样的咖啡?不加牛奶的还是加牛奶的? 3. His hands were black from working on the car all afternoon. 他的双手因为整个下午都在修车而变得脏黑黑的。 4. His father looked as black as thunder. 他的父亲看上去极为愤怒。 5. The black shows up against the white. 在白色的衬托下,黑色很显目。 6. The unions have blacked all inports from country. 工会拒绝处理从这个国家进口的一切货物。', '形容词: blackish 副词: blackly 名词: blackness 过去式: blacked 过去分词: blacked 现在分词: blacking 第三人称单数: blacks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('promise', '[\'prɑːmɪs]', 'n.诺言；预示；约定；(有)希望 v.允诺；发誓；答应；有希望', '1. Once he made a promise, he would stick to it. 他一旦许下诺言,就坚守这个诺言。 2. I have committed myself and must keep my promise. 我已经作出了承诺,必须信守我的诺言。 3. I don\'t trust his promise to come for a visit. 我不相信他会如约前来访问。 4. For her family, life seemed to have no promise. 对她家而言,生活没有任何希望。 5. I promise never to reveal his secret. 我答应决不泄漏他的秘密。', '名词: promiser 过去式: promised 过去分词: promised 现在分词: promising 第三人称单数: promises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dorm', '[dɔːrm]', 'n.(集体)宿舍', '1. She\'s not feeling well and is staying in the dorm. 她感觉不舒服，因此呆在宿舍里。 2. You will find our dorm a home from home. 你将会觉得在我们宿舍就像呆在家一样舒适。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('selfish', '[\'selfɪʃ]', 'adj.自私的；利己的', '1. A selfish person always thinks about himself. 一个自私的人总是想着自己。 2. I am becoming more and more irritated by his selfish behaviour. 我对他那种自私的行为愈加恼火起来。 3. I call his behaviour mean and selfish. 我认为他的行为卑鄙、 自私。 4. Nobody but you could be so selfish. 除了你之外，谁也不会这样自私。', '副词: selfishly 名词: selfishness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pork', '[pɔːrk]', 'n.猪肉', '1. The little girl only eats lean pork. 这个小女孩只吃瘦肉。 2. In some religions pork is considered impure. 某些宗教认为猪肉是亵渎的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('favorite', '[\'feɪvərɪt]', 'adj.喜爱的；流行的 n.最喜爱的人或物；最有希望获胜的选手', '1. My favorite pastime is reading. 我最喜爱的消遣是读书。 2. Mark Twain is his favorite writer. 马克•吐温是他最喜爱的作家。 3. Purple is the favorite color for young ladies this year. 今年紫色在年轻女士们当中很受欢迎。 4. I like all the books on the shelf but this one is my favorite. 我喜欢书架上所有的书，但这本是我最喜欢的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nursery', '[\'nɜːrsəri]', 'n.托儿所；保育室；苗圃', '1. Many children under five go to nursery school. 5岁以下的许多儿童都上幼儿园。 2. She\'s all for more nursery schools being built. 她坚持主张多建托儿所。 3. She sent her little son to a nursery when she was working. 她工作的时候就把小儿子送到托儿所。 4. We bought a small tree at the nursery. 我们在苗圃买了一棵小树。', '名词复数: nurseries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mess', '[mes]', 'n.混乱；混杂；脏乱；一份食品；粪便；（军队的）食堂 v.弄糟；弄乱；妨碍', '1. The local economy is now in a mess. 当地的经济现在很混乱。 2. The heavy rain made a great mess of the garden. 这场大雨把花园搞得一团糟。 3. The room was in a terrible mess. 房间里脏乱不堪。 4. He caught a large mess of fish. 他捕到足够饱餐一顿的鱼。 5. I am ask to organize the trip, but I mess it up. 大家要我组织这次旅游, 可是我把事情搞糟了。', '过去式: messed 过去分词: messed 现在分词: messing 第三人称单数: messes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('settlement', '[\'setlmənt]', 'n.解决；结算；协议；安置；殖民；定居', '1. There is no prospect of a settlement of the dispute. 这场纠纷根本不可能获得解决。 2. Negotiators are looking for a peaceful settlement to the dispute. 谈判双方正寻求和平解决争端的办法。 3. After much discussion the negotiators hammered out a compromise settlement. 双方经多次谈判达成一项折衷的解决办法。 4. I enclose a cheque in settlement of your account. 兹附支票一张以结清贵处帐目。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('savage', '[\'sævɪdʒ]', 'adj.野性的；凶猛的；粗鲁的；荒野的；原始的 n.野蛮人；粗人；凶恶的人 vt.激烈抨击；猛烈攻击', '1. Most of the time elephants are tame but they can be very savage. 大多数时候大象很温顺,但他们也会大发野性。 2. He was wild and savage, and no man could mount him, or do anything at all with him. 它既野又凶，谁都驾驭不了它，谁也对它没办法。 3. He smarted from the savage attacks on his film. 他因自己的影片受到猛烈攻击而感到痛心。 4. She was irritated by his savage behavior. 他的不文明行为激怒了她。 5. These civilizations flourished while Europeans were still savages living in caves. 当欧洲人还是居住在洞穴中的野蛮人时，这些地方的文化早已十分繁荣昌盛。 6. Smith\'s play was savaged by the critics. 史密斯的剧本遭到评论家的猛烈抨击。', '副词: savagely 名词: savageness 过去式: savaged 过去分词: savaged 现在分词: savaging 第三人称单数: savages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fund', '[fʌnd]', 'n.基金 vt.资助；转为（长期贷款）', '1. Our company is in want of fund. 我们的公司需要资金。 2. The pension fund owns shares in several major public companies. 该养老基金在几家主要出售股份给公众的公司中均有股份。 3. The factory has built up reserve fund. 这个工厂已积累了后备基金。 4. A fund will be set up for the dead men\'s families. 抚恤死难工人家属的基金会即将建立起来。 5. The National Asthma Campaign is funding research into allergy and air pollution. 国家哮喘运动组织为对过敏和空气污染进行研究提供基金。', '过去式: funded 过去分词: funded 现在分词: funding 第三人称单数: funds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sentiment', '[\'sentɪmənt]', 'n.情绪；感情；观点；感伤', '1. He could feel the sentiment stirring within him. 他可以感觉到这种情绪在心中波动。 2. His speech loosed a tide of nationalist sentiment. 他的讲话表露出一种强烈的民族主义情绪。 3. He could not adequately express his sentiment. 他无法恰当地表达出他的感情。 4. What are his sentiments on this issue? 他对这个问题持什么观点？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lucky', '[\'lʌki]', 'adj.幸运的；带来好运的', '1. You lucky blighter! 你这幸运的家伙！ 2. He is really a lucky dog. 他真是个幸运的家伙。 3. You are lucky to be alive after being in that accident. 你真幸运，经过那场车祸还能生还。 4. Some people seem to be always lucky. 有些人似乎从来是幸运的。', '比较级: luckier 最高级: luckiest 名词: luckiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lecture', '[\'lektʃər]', 'n.讲课；演讲；训话 v.训斥；讲课；教导', '1. She ran over her notes before giving the lecture. 她讲课前把讲稿匆匆看了一遍。 2. His lecture covered various aspects of language. 他的讲课涉及到语言诸方面的问题。 3. They could not follow the lecture. 他们听不懂这次演讲。 4. He wrote down the outline of his lecture. 他写下演讲的提纲。 5. It was a shame for me to be lectured in front of the whole class. 当着整个班级的面被训斥了一顿，真让我感到羞辱。', '过去式: lectured 过去分词: lectured 现在分词: lecturing 第三人称单数: lectures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consent', '[kən\'sent]', 'n.同意；赞成 v.同意；答应', '1. My father will never give his consent to our marriage. 我父亲决不会同意我们的婚姻的。 2. By the common consent of critics, Shakespeare is the prince of character delineators. 评论家一致公认莎士比亚是刻画人物的大师。 3. Her smile implied her consent to our proposal. 她的微笑暗示她赞成我们的提议。 4. On the other hand, it is not likely that the few landlords from the upper strata of the Miao nationality will consent to their demand. 但是这样的要求，可能苗族上层少数地主分子不赞成。 5. I\'m sure he wouldn\'t consent 我确信他不会同意。', '名词: consenter 过去式: consented 过去分词: consented 现在分词: consenting 第三人称单数: consents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('specific', '[spə\'sɪfɪk]', 'adj.明确的；特殊的；具有特效的 n.特效药；详情；特性', '1. He gave us very specific instructions. 他给我们做了非常明确的指示。 2. This tells you that there is a specific distinction between the right and the wrong. 这件事告诉你是与非是有明确的区别的。 3. Let us take a look at three specific areas of concern. 让我们看一看三个特殊的令人关切的领域。 4. There is no specific remedy for the malady. 没有医治这种病的特效药。 5. This is a specific for cancer. 这是一种治疗癌症的特效药。', '副词: specifically 名词: specificity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('through', '[θruː]', 'adv.通过；径直；自始至终；(电话)接通；完全 prep.穿过；凭借；一直到 adj.直达的；直通的；贯穿的；完成的；结束的', '1. The crowd fell back to let the players through. 人群后退让运动员们通过。 2. Put the coffee in the filter and let the water through. 把咖啡放入过滤器里让水流过。 3. \"Did you stop in Oxford on the way?\"\"No, we drove straight through.\" “你们路径牛津时停车了吗？”“没有，我们一直来过来的。” 4. Don\'t tell me how it ends--I haven\'t read all the way through yet. 先别告诉我书的结尾--我还没看完呢。 5. The ball went through the window. 那球穿过窗子飞去。 6. Welcome on board the 94 through train to Guangzhou. 欢迎乘坐开往广州去的94次直达列车。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fume', '[fjuːm]', 'n.烟；汽；愤怒 v.冒烟；愤怒', '1. The fireman was suffocated by the fumes. 那个消防队员让浓烟憋死了。 2. The fume caused by coalburning is one of the main air pollutants in China. 燃煤烟尘是我国最主要的大气污染物之一。 3. The ground was hidden by a white fume. 地面上笼罩着一层白色的水汽。 4. Mother was in a fume this morning. 今天早上妈妈很生气。 5. The burnt heaps of wood were still fuming. 燃烧的木堆仍在冒着烟。', '过去式: fumed 过去分词: fumed 现在分词: fuming 第三人称单数: fumes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bus', '[bʌs]', 'n.公共汽车 n.总线；信息通路 vt.用公共汽车运输 vi.乘公共汽车', '1. The busman stopped the bus. 公共汽车司机停下了车。 2. The bus driver asked the passengers to buy tickets. 公共汽车司机要求乘客买票。 3. Nor can you always use bus interrupts. 你也不可能总是用总线中断。 4. My bike to the bus station. Then I bus to work. 我骑自行车去汽车站,然后乘早班车去上班。', '名词复数: buses 过去式: bused/bussed 过去分词: bused/bussed 现在分词: busing/bussing 第三人称单数: buses/busses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('polish', '[\'pɑːlɪʃ]', 'n.光泽；上光剂；优雅；精良 v.擦亮；磨光；推敲；完善 Polish. adj.波兰的；波兰人的；波兰语的 n.波兰语', '1. A hot plate will spoil the polish on this table. 热盘子会毁坏桌面的光泽。 2. This car polish is an effective shield against rust. 这种汽车上光蜡很有防锈作用。 3. With this polish you can give a good high gloss to the wood. 使用这种上光蜡可使木器表面极为光亮平滑。 4. Now we have a presentable great speaker whose polish reminds me of Will Smith. 现在我们能言善辩的总统，他的优雅一直让我想起了威尔史密斯。 5. I polished my buttons with a handkerchief. 我用手帕把钮扣擦亮。 6. When I awoke, a Polish man came to my room, held my hand and looked at me with friendly eyes. 当我醒来时,一名波兰人走过来,他握着我的手,亲切地望着我。 7. My spoken Polish is better than my written Polish. 我的波兰语说得比写得好。', '名词: polisher 过去式: polished 过去分词: polished 现在分词: polishing 第三人称单数: polishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('philosophy', '[fə\'lɑːsəfi]', 'n.哲学；哲理', '1. This organization espouses the socialist philosophy. 这个组织支持社会主义哲学。 2. He holds the chair of philosophy at Oxford. 他任牛津大学哲学教授。 3. He regarded it as with profound philosophy. 他认为这里面有深奥的哲理。', '名词复数: philosophies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('devote', '[dɪ\'voʊt]', 'vt.致力于；奉献给；把...专用于', '1. You must devote your attention to your work. 你必须专心于工作。 2. After he graduated, he continued to devote himself to the research. 毕业以后,他继续潜心于这项研究。 3. He devoted himself entirely to music. 他将一生奉献给了音乐。 4. He started to study ecology and decided to devote his whole life to the science. 他开始研究生态学,并决心将他的一生献身于这门学科。', '名词: devotement 过去式: devoted 过去分词: devoted 现在分词: devoting 第三人称单数: devotes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compartment', '[kəm\'pɑːrtmənt]', 'n.间隔；个别室；卧车包房 vt.划分', '1. This is a case with separate compartments for shoes, jewelry, etc. 这是一个分格存放鞋、珠宝等的箱子。 2. and the rats move into the front compartment. 老鼠就会移入前间隔间。 3. Since there was no one else in the compartment I was able to spread myself. 车厢间隔里没有别人，我正好能伸胳膊伸腿舒坦一下。 4. The first-class compartments are in the front of the train. 头等车室在列车的前面。 5. Life today is compartmented into work and leisure. 现今生活分成工作和闲暇两部分。', '形容词: compartmental 过去式: compartmented 过去分词: compartmented 现在分词: compartmenting 第三人称单数: compartments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('theirs', '[ðerz]', 'pron.他(她；它)们的', '1. Theirs are blue. 他们的是蓝色的。 2. Our house adjoins theirs. 我们的房屋与他们的毗连。 3. It was his fault, not theirs. 这是他的过错，不是他们的。 4. They were off to visit a friend of theirs. 他们动身去拜访他们的朋友。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('too', '[tuː]', 'adv.也；太；而且；很', '1. I will go, provided that you go too. 你也去的话我就去。 2. It\'s too early for getting up. 现在起床还太早。 3. She broke her leg last week-and on her birthday too! 她上星期把腿摔断了，而且还是在她生日那一天！ 4. I know too well that I get on her tits. 我很明白自己惹怒了她。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('length', '[leŋθ]', 'n.长度；时间长短；距离；一段；距离的测量单位', '1. plough the field 2. The room is 15 feet in length and 10 feet in breadth. 这房间长15英尺，宽10英尺。 3. The length of your talk must be at least 10 minutes. 你的演讲时间至少要保持在10分钟。 4. The pier was lit up along its entire length. 整个桥墩从头到尾都沐浴在灯火之中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slum', '[slʌm]', 'n.贫民窟 vi.访问贫民区', '1. They\'ve demolished the slum district. 贫民区已拆除。 2. The bar in the slum is a den of iniquity. 这个贫民窟里的小酒吧是一个充满罪恶的场所。 3. The slum area was sordid and filthy beyond belief. 该贫民区之污秽肮脏简直令人难以置信。 4. She could not speak the jargon of the slum. 她不会讲贫民区的黑话。', '形容词: slummy 名词: slummer 过去式: slummed 过去分词: slummed 现在分词: slumming 第三人称单数: slums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('upgrade', '[ˌʌp\'ɡreɪd]', 'vt.升级；提高；改善 adv.向上地 n.升级；上坡', '1. Please click here to upgrade your Player. 请单击此处,升级您的播放器。 2. Companies need to upgrade servers. 公司需要对服务器升级。 3. We need to upgrade the pay and status of teachers. 我们需要提高教师的工资和地位。 4. We must try to upgrade our cattle to the required standard of meat. 我们必须努力提高牛的品级，使之达到所要求的食用肉标准。 5. After a short break, the climbers continued upgrade. 稍事休息後,攀登者们继续往山上走。 6. The power plant received a new upgrade. 那个电厂进行了一次升级改造。', '过去式: upgraded 过去分词: upgraded 现在分词: upgrading 第三人称单数: upgrades');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('another', '[ə\'nʌðər]', 'adj.另一的；再一个的 pron.另一个；类似的一个；别的', '1. It is just as well that you took another road. 还好你们走了另一条路。 2. She has been transferred to another department. 她已被调往另一个部门。 3. Will you like another cup of tea? 你要再来一杯茶吗？ 4. The agreement has been renewed for another year. 该协定的期限已经再延长一年。 5. I don\'t like this one. Please show me another 我不喜欢这个，请给我另一个。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weld', '[weld]', 'v.焊接；使结合 n.焊接；焊缝', '1. Weld abandoned tools onto the wheel. 把废弃的工具焊接上车轮。 2. His job is to weld parts together. 他的工作是焊接零件。 3. They weld the pieces of a broken axle. 他们焊接断了的车轴。 4. His job is to weld parts together. 他的工作是焊接零件。', '名词: welder 过去式: welded 过去分词: welded 现在分词: welding 第三人称单数: welds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('July', '[dʒu\'laɪ]', 'n.七月', '1. July is the hottest month in a year in my hometown. 在我的家乡，七月是一年里最热的一月。 2. The maximum temperature in July may be 36 Celsius degree. 七月份最高温度可能达到36摄氏度。 3. He will leave at the end of term, to wit 30 July. 他要在期末离开，也就是7月30日。 4. The Forth of July is the National Independence Day of the USA. 七月四日是美国国庆日。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('moist', '[mɔɪst]', 'adj.潮湿的；湿润的；[医]湿性的', '1. This gave a warm and moist feeling to the picture. 这样让整张画有了些温暖和潮湿的感觉。 2. Winds from the sea are usually moist. 海风通常是潮湿的。 3. There is a moist wind from the sea. 海上吹来了一阵湿润的风。 4. The story was so sad that at the end my eyes were moist with tears. 故事非常让人伤心,最后我的眼睛湿润了。', '副词: moistly 比较级: moister 最高级: moistest 名词: moistness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('morning', '[\'mɔːrnɪŋ]', 'n.早晨；上午；开端', '1. Did you really feel ill this morning? 今天早晨你真的感到身体不适吗？ 2. He is loath to get out of bed on cold morning. 在寒冷的早晨他讨厌起床。 3. The people next door play their radio from morning till night. 邻居从早到晚开着收音机。 4. I\'ll ring her up in the morning. 我明天上午给她打电话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quarrel', '[\'kwɔːrəl]', 'n.吵架；争论；怨言 vi.吵架；争论；挑剔', '1. He seemed determined to pick a quarrel with us. 他似乎存心要找我们吵架。 2. They were reconciled after a quarrel. 他们吵架之后又重归于好。 3. Their small argument boiled over into a serious quarrel. 他们的小争论终于酿成了一场激烈的争吵。 4. I got involved in a quarrel about the price. 我被卷入了一场有关价格的争吵。 5. The couple was quarreling furiously about whose turn it was to cook the dinner. 这对夫妇对该轮到谁做晚饭而激烈争吵着。', '名词: quarreler 过去式: quarreled/quarrelled 过去分词: quarreled/quarrelled 现在分词: quarreling/quarrelling 第三人称单数: quarrels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alcohol', '[\'ælkəhɔːl]', 'n.酒精；酒；乙醇', '1. Whisky contains a large percentage of alcohol. 威士忌所含酒精的百分比很高。 2. Alcohol has a very bad effect on drivers. 酒精对司机的影响很大。 3. This substance is soluble in alcohol. 这种物质能够溶解在酒精中。 4. He is addicted to alcohol. 他嗜好喝酒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('natural', '[\'nætʃrəl]', 'adj.自然的；天然的；私生的', '1. It is natural that he should fall in love with such a beautiful girl. 他爱上那位美丽的姑娘是很自然的事。 2. I prefer to see animals living in their natural state. 我宁愿看处于野生状态的动物。 3. Leave her alone. She\'s natural crier. 别理她,她是个天生爱哭的人。 4. Harriet Smith was the natural daughter of somebody. 哈里特·史密斯是一位不知姓名的人的非婚生女。', '名词: naturalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reed', '[riːd]', 'n.芦苇；芦笛；簧片 Reed：里德（姓氏）.', '1. Hope is a slender reed for a stout man to lean on. 希望是壮汉依靠的一根纤细的芦苇。 2. The river banks were overgrown with reed. 河岸长满了芦苇。 3. Only let me make my life simple and straight, like a flute of reed for thee to fill with music. 只容我把自己的生命归做率真坦荡，象一只芦笛被你盈满乐音。 4. Whether an invaluable Italian violin or a casually-cut reed whistle, when left untouched, remains soundless. 一把价值连城的意大利提琴，和一枝被随手削出的芦笛，不去触动它们，便都是沉默，但沉默的内涵却并不一样。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('communism', '[\'kɑːmjunɪzəm]', 'n.共产主义', '1. Communism is based on Marxism. 共产主义是以马克思主义为基础。 2. Our ultimate aim is to realize communism. 我们的最终目的是实现共产主义。 3. Marx is the progenitor of Communism. 马克思是共产主义的创始人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inlet', '[\'ɪnlet]', 'n.水湾；入口；插入物 vt.引进；插入', '1. The tide flushed through this narrow inlet. 潮水涌过了狭窄的小湾。 2. Here is just the fuel inlet. 这儿正是燃料入口。 3. There\'s only one inlet to the parking lot. 这个停车场只有一个入口。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('farm', '[fɑːrm]', 'n.农场；农田 v.务农', '1. We work on the farm. 我们在农场工作。 2. Increasingly, farm land is yielding to property development. 地产的发展逐渐占据了农田。 3. Our farm land was adjacent to the river. 我们的农田在河边。 4. My friend is farming in Wales. 我的朋友在威尔士的农场种地。', '过去式: farmed 过去分词: farmed 现在分词: farming 第三人称单数: farms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('napkin', '[\'næpkɪn]', 'n.餐巾；一小块布或毛巾；卫生巾', '1. I need another plate and a napkin. 我再要一只碟子和一条餐巾。 2. He wipes his mouth on the napkin. 他用餐巾擦了擦嘴， 3. The mother laid a piece of napkin under the baby\'s body. 这位母亲在婴儿的身体下面铺了一块尿布。 4. According to the demand, it can produce ultra-thin cotton-core or leakage Barrier sanitary napkin. 根据要求可装配超薄棉芯卫生巾，可装配立体护围面料成型。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('linguistic', '[lɪŋ\'ɡwɪstɪk]', 'adj.语言的；语言学的', '1. Gorbachev is a master of linguistic gestures. 戈尔巴乔夫精于语言的动作。 2. Thereafter, his linguistic abilities would decrease as he gets older. 年纪越大，掌握语言的能力相对的也越低。 3. She is pursuing her linguistic researches. 她在从事语言学的研究。 4. Viewed from the perspective of postcolonial translation studies, it is no more a purely aesthetic or linguistic act. 后殖民翻译研究视野中的翻译不再是纯美学的或纯语言学的行为。', '副词: linguistically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('perpetual', '[pər\'petʃuəl]', 'adj.永久的；永恒的；一再往复的', '1. He was perpetual president of the country. 他是该国的终身总统。 2. He has run his course and takes his perpetual rest. 他已走完他的行程而长眠了。 3. She lives in perpetual fear of being discovered. 她永远生活在怕被发现的恐惧中。 4. It is the secret of perpetual youth. 它是青春永驻的秘诀。', '副词: perpetually');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mutton', '[\'mʌtn]', 'n.羊肉', '1. Fish doesn\'t go well with mutton. 鱼和羊肉在一起不好吃。 2. People like to have mutton in the winter. 冬天人们喜欢吃羊肉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nominate', '[\'nɑːmɪneɪt]', 'vt.提名；指派；登记赛马参加比赛', '1. I nominate Bill for the club president. 我提名比尔为俱乐部主席候选人。 2. Only students may nominate someone for the award. 只有学生才可以提名一些教师去拿这个奖项。 3. The board nominated him as the new director. 董事会指定他为新董事。', '名词: nominator 过去式: nominated 过去分词: nominated 现在分词: nominating 第三人称单数: nominates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remarkable', '[rɪ\'mɑːrkəbl]', 'adj.非凡的；值得注意的；显著的；异常的；卓越的', '1. The book is filled with remarkable insights. 这本书很有真知卓见。 2. He showed remarkable courage when he faced the danger. 他在面对危险的时候表现出非凡的勇气。 3. The changes taking place in China is remarkable. 中国发生的变化是值得注意的。 4. Science has made remarkable progress. 科学有了显著的进步。', '副词: remarkably 名词: remarkableness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sturdy', '[\'stɜːrdi]', 'adj.强健的；坚固的；坚决的', '1. The sturdy young man removed the rock without effort. 那个壮实的小伙子没费多大劲便把石块搬开了。 2. His son has grown up into a sturdy hardworking young man. 他的儿子已成长为一个健壮勤劳的小伙子。 3. That chair doesn\'t look very sturdy. 椅子看上其不坚固。 4. Have you any sturdy hiking boots? 有没有耐用的健行靴？', '副词: sturdily 比较级: sturdier 最高级: sturdiest 名词: sturdiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ability', '[ə\'bɪləti]', 'n.能力；才能', '1. This is a task well within your ability. 这完全是你力所能及的工作。 2. She has the ability to keep calm in an emergency. 她有处变不惊的本事。 3. He is a man of great executive ability. 他是个具有极高管理才能的人。 4. The boy shows remarkable ability at math. 这男孩显示出非凡的数学才能。', '名词复数: abilities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tilt', '[tɪlt]', 'vt.(使)倾斜 vi.抨击；争论 n.倾斜；车盖；以全速；(小舟、车辆、地摊等的)帐蓬', '1. Don\'t tilt your chair back so far, it might fall over. 别把椅子一个劲向后倾斜，它会翻倒的。 2. If you tilt the table,the dishes will slide off onto the floor. 如果你使桌子倾斜，碟子就会滑到地板上。 3. The table top suddenly tilted and all the plates and glasses crashed onto the floor. 桌面突然翘起，所有的盘子和玻璃制品都滑落到地板上打碎了。 4. Tilt pump downward and remove from engine. 将泵向下倾斜，从引擎移出。 5. He is bold enough to tilt at social injustices. 他敢于抨击社会上的不公正现象。 6. Such a tilt is unusual in the solar system. 这样的倾斜在太阳系中不常见。', '名词: tilter 过去式: tilted 过去分词: tilted 现在分词: tilting 第三人称单数: tilts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('detain', '[dɪ\'teɪn]', 'vt.扣留；拘押；耽搁；延误', '1. You cannot detain the eagle in the forest. 你没有法子将一只老鹰扣留在森林里。 2. We shall have to detain him and question him. 我们只好把他扣起来，讯问他一下。 3. Allow me to detain you for a moment. 请允许我耽搁你一会儿。 4. This matter isn\'t very important, and shouldn\'t detain us very long. 这事不很重要，不该耽搁我们很久。', '名词: detainment 过去式: detained 过去分词: detained 现在分词: detaining 第三人称单数: detains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unite', '[ju\'naɪt]', 'v.联合；合并；统一；团结', '1. They unite to form a new company. 他们联合组成一个新公司。 2. The more of the masses we unite with, the better. 我们联合起来的群众越多，就越有利。 3. Two major telecommunication providers will unite into one. 两大主要的电信提供商会合并成一家。 4. The oceans do not divide the world so much as unite it. 与其说是海洋分割这个世界,不如说是统一这个世界。', '过去式: united 过去分词: united 现在分词: uniting 第三人称单数: unites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spectacular', '[spek\'tækjələr]', 'adj.壮观的；令人惊叹的 n.壮观；豪华节目', '1. We watched a spectacular sunset at the beach. 我们在海边欣赏了非常壮观的日落。 2. The view from the top of the tower was spectacular. 从塔顶远眺景色蔚为壮观。 3. The dragon dance in the town square was really spectacular. 城市广场上的舞龙,真是令人叹为观止。 4. Their performance in the championship last night was spectacular. 他们昨晚在锦标赛的表现十分引人注目。 5. We watched a spectacular sunset at the beach. 我们在海边欣赏了非常壮观的日落。', '副词: spectacularly 名词: spectacularity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tuition', '[tu\'ɪʃn]', 'n.学费；教诲；教学', '1. The money is sufficient to cover the tuition. 这笔钱够付学费。 2. She relies on her parents for tuition. 她的学费依赖于父母。 3. Thank you for your tuition. 谢谢您的教诲。 4. Mary has derived a lot of benefit from her tuition. 玛丽从她的教学中得到很大收益。', '形容词: tuitional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('infectious', '[ɪn\'fekʃəs]', 'adj.传染的；有感染力的', '1. Measles is an infectious disease. 麻疹是种传染病。 2. When you have this anthema, you are still infectious. 身上还有这种疹子就仍然有传染性。 3. Flu is an infectious disease characterized by fever, aches and pains and exhaustion. 流感是一种传染病，其特征是发热、全身疼痛和疲乏无力。 4. He expressed infectious enthusiasm to his voters. 他对他的选民表现出很有感染力的热情。', '副词: infectiously 名词: infectiousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('confidence', '[\'kɑːnfɪdəns]', 'n.信任；把握；信心；知心话 adj.骗得信任的', '1. The servant enjoyed his master\'s confidence. 这仆人深得主人的信赖。 2. We have full confidence that we shall succeed. 我们完全有把握取得成功。 3. The worst barrier to your success is not lack of money, but lack of confidence. 你成功最大的障碍不是缺钱,而是缺乏信心。 4. The two girls told each other confidences about their boyfriends. 这两个姑娘相互谈了关于各自男友的悄悄话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elder', '[\'eldər]', 'adj.年龄较大的；年长的 n.长者；长辈；[植]接骨木', '1. He is the elder twin of the two. 他是两个双胞胎较年长的那个。 2. The elder welder seldom yields his field. 年长的焊接工很少放弃他的场地。 3. He is the elder of the twins. 他是双胞胎中的哥哥。 4. An elder interfered to stop the argument. 一位长者出面干预，以平息这场争论。', '名词: eldership');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('swan', '[swɑːn]', 'n.天鹅 vi.闲荡；游荡', '1. A black swan is rare. 黑天鹅很稀有。 2. The swan sings when death comes. 死期来到，天鹅歌声美妙。 3. The witch turned the princess into a swan. 巫婆把公主变成了一只天鹅。 4. Are you swanning off on holiday again? 你又是一走了之度假去了吗?', '过去式: swanned 过去分词: swanned 现在分词: swanning 第三人称单数: swans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('broadcast', '[\'brɔːdkæst]', 'v.广播；散布；撒播 n.广播；广播节目', '1. The chairman\'s speech will be broadcast nationwide. 主席的讲话将向全国广播。 2. She broadcasts on current affairs. 她发表时事广播演说。 3. The BBC broadcasts all over the world. 英国广播公司向全世界播送节目。 4. Before this play is broadcast several cuts must be made. 这个剧目播出前必须经过数次剪辑。 5. The broadcast was recorded, not live. 这次广播是事先录音的，不是现场直播。', '名词: broadcaster 过去式: broadcast/broadcasted 过去分词: broadcast/broadcasted 现在分词: broadcasting 第三人称单数: broadcasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lack', '[læk]', 'n.缺乏；无 v.缺乏；不足', '1. Her decision seems to show a lack of political judgement. 她的决定似乎显示出缺乏政治判断力。 2. Lack of sun retards plant growth. 光照不足则植物生长缓慢。 3. In a cold winter, many wild animals can die from lack of food. 在严寒的冬天,很多野生动物可能因缺乏食物而死去。 4. I tell you, people will lack the means to live. 我告诉你,人们将缺乏生活资料。', '过去式: lacked 过去分词: lacked 现在分词: lacking 第三人称单数: lacks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fertilizer', '[\'fɜːrtəlaɪzər]', 'n.肥料', '1. The stalks will rot and make good fertilizer. 杆儿腐烂后会成为很好的肥料。 2. Crushed bones make one of the best fertilizers. 碎骨是最好的肥料之一。 3. Farmers bartered rice for fertilizer. 农民们用大米换肥料。 4. The tractor hauled the fertilizer away. 拖拉机把肥料拉走了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extreme', '[ɪk\'striːm]', 'adj.极度的；极端的 n.极端；极限', '1. Extreme cold can wake a hibernating animal. 极度的寒冷能使正在冬眠的动物苏醒。 2. The extreme heat sapped his strength and health. 极度的暑热逐渐损耗他的体力兴健康。 3. Extreme poverty had reduced them to a state of apathy. 极端的贫困使他们万念俱灰。 4. The capital is in the extreme south of the country. 首都在这个国家的最南端。 5. Love and hate are extremes. 爱和恨是两个极端。', '副词: extremely 名词: extremeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prison', '[\'prɪzn]', 'n.监狱；监禁 vt.囚禁；关入监狱', '1. The police crushed out the rebellion in the prison. 警察把发生在监狱中的暴乱镇压了下去。 2. That felon tried to escape from the prison. 那名重罪犯试图从监狱中逃跑。 3. His deliverance from the prison puzzled us. 他被从监狱释放使我们困惑不已。 4. Strikes by prison officers underline the need for reform in our gaols. 监狱工作人员罢工一事，突出地表明我们的监狱制度需要改革。 5. She continues to languish in a foreign prison. 她被继续囚禁在一所外国的监狱里。', '过去式: prisoned 过去分词: prisoned 现在分词: prisoning 第三人称单数: prisons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prestige', '[pre\'stiːʒ]', 'n.[U]威望；声望 adj.有威信的；名贵的', '1. She enjoyed high prestige among the masses. 她在群众中享有很高威信。 2. He is an author of international prestige. 他是有国际声望的作家。 3. The old universities of Oxford and Cambridge still have a lot of prestige. 历史悠久的牛津大学和剑桥大学仍然享有很高的声望。 4. The company would do anything but risk their prestige at stake. 公司绝不愿将自己的信誉孤注一掷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anchor', '[\'æŋkər]', 'n.锚；锚状物；依靠；新闻节目主播；压阵队员 v.抛锚；停泊；用锚系住；担任（广播电视新闻节目）的主持人', '1. The ship dragged its anchor during the night. 夜里,船把锚拖动了。 2. Hope is his only anchor. 希望是他唯一的依靠。 3. He was then doing the anchor. 他当时正主持新闻广播节目。 4. The anchor man in a relay team runs last. 接力队中的主力跑最后一棒。 5. The ship was anchored off the shore. 船在海岸处抛了锚。', '过去式: anchored 过去分词: anchored 现在分词: anchoring 第三人称单数: anchors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rotate', '[\'roʊteɪt]', 'v.轮流；(使)旋转 adj.车轮状的', '1. The post of chairman rotates among members of the committee. 主席一职由委员会的成员轮流担任。 2. Interns have to rotate for a few months. 实习医生轮流工作了几个月。 3. He rotates the handle gently. 他轻轻地转动手柄。 4. Does the earth rotate on an axis? 地球是绕轴旋转的吗？', '形容词: rotatable 过去式: rotated 过去分词: rotated 现在分词: rotating 第三人称单数: rotates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('though', '[ðoʊ]', 'conj.虽然；尽管；然而；可是 adv.（用在句末补充说明使语气减弱）不过', '1. Though we have tried our best, we lost the game. 虽然我们已尽了最大的力量,但还是输了。 2. I don\'t know him well though I\'ve known him for a long time. 我对他并不了解，虽然我认识他已经很长时间了。 3. Though the task was difficult,they managed to accomplish it on time. 尽管任务困难,他们仍按时完成了。 4. They will probably win, though no one thinks so. 他们可能会获胜，然而没有人这样认为。 5. He said he would come, he didn\'t, though. 他说他要来，可是并没有来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rush', '[rʌʃ]', 'v.冲；仓促行事；突袭；奔；急速流动 n.抢购；匆忙；冲进；急速行进；蜂拥 adj.繁忙的；紧急的', '1. I really hate to rush off like this. 我真的不喜欢这样匆匆离去。 2. They rushed up the stairs. 他们冲到楼上。 3. He did not like us to rush him. 他不喜欢我们催他。 4. Don\'t rush at your work or you will spoil it. 不要匆忙地做你的工作，否则你会把它做坏的。 5. There was a rush for the concert tickets. 出现了争购音乐会入场券的热潮。 6. Our manager became a slave driver during the rush season. 赶定单的季节,我们的经理就变得苛刻,只晓得逼人拼命干活。', '名词: rusher 过去式: rushed 过去分词: rushed 现在分词: rushing 第三人称单数: rushes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bathe', '[beɪð]', 'v.沐浴；用水洗；沉浸', '1. And when Sparta burns, you shall bathe in gold. 当斯巴达被火烧的时候，你们讲沐浴在黄金里。 2. The doctor advised him to bathe in the sun.s rays. 医生劝他沐浴阳光。 3. He took some time to bathe in short stories. 他花了些时间沉浸在短篇小说里。', '名词: bather 过去式: bathed 过去分词: bathed 现在分词: bathing 第三人称单数: bathes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pilot', '[\'paɪlət]', 'n.飞行员；领航员；试播节目；<美>排障器；[机]导向器 v.驾驶；领航；向导；试点 adj.试验性的；引导的', '1. A pilot must be awake to the changes in the weather. 飞行员必须警觉天气的变化。 2. Mark used to be a pilot on the Mississippi River. 马克曾在密西西比河上当过领航员。 3. JULES I think her biggest deal was she starred in a pilot. 朱尔斯：我想她最重要的演出是在一个试片里担任主角。 4. When did you learn to pilot an airplane? 你什么时候学会驾驶飞机的? 5. We are doing a pilot study to see if the new product will sell well. 我们正在为这种新产品做试销调查，看它的销路好不好。', '过去式: piloted 过去分词: piloted 现在分词: piloting 第三人称单数: pilots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('presume', '[prɪ\'zuːm]', 'vt.假定；推测；姑且认定；认为是理所当然 vi.越权行事；利用', '1. The law presumes innocence until guilt is proved. 在罪状未证实前，法律假定被告无罪。 2. We presume that the factory has been fully engaged. 我们推测工厂的生产已经满负荷了。 3. That\'s the new assistant, I presume. 我想那就是新来的助理 4. I presume that this is your final answer. 我认为这就是你最后的答复。 5. May I presume to advise you? 我可以冒昧向你进一言吗？', '副词: presumedly 名词: presumer 过去式: presumed 过去分词: presumed 现在分词: presuming 第三人称单数: presumes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sour', '[\'saʊər]', 'adj.酸的；酸腐的；刻薄的 v.变酸', '1. Most green fruit is sour. 大多数未熟的水果都是酸的。 2. The dish\'s gone sour. 这菜已经变质了。 3. He\'s always got a sour look on his face, and he has never said anything friendly. 他总是板着脸,从来不说一句好听的话。 4. The hot weather has soured the milk. 炎热的天气使牛奶变酸了。', '形容词: sourish 副词: sourly 比较级: sourer 最高级: sourest 名词: sourness 过去式: soured 过去分词: soured 现在分词: souring 第三人称单数: sours');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pardon', '[\'pɑːrdn]', 'n.原谅，宽恕，饶恕；赦免，赦免状 vt.原谅；宽恕，饶恕；赦免，免于治罪', '1. I do beg your pardon. 一定请您原谅。 2. She supplicated for pardon. 她恳求原谅。 3. They all sued out a pardon for an offender. 他们请求法院赦免一名罪犯。 4. He begged a pardon from the king. 他恳求国王赦免自己的罪行。 5. Pardon my strong language, please. 请原谅我说了激烈的话。', '形容词: pardonable 副词: pardonably 名词: pardonableness 过去式: pardoned 过去分词: pardoned 现在分词: pardoning 第三人称单数: pardons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('between', '[bɪ\'twiːn]', 'prep.在 ... 之间 adv.在中间', '1. Children must attend school between 5 and 16. 5至16岁的孩子必须上学。 2. There is a generation gap between my parents and I. 我父母和我之间有代沟。 3. She tried to intervene between her husband and son. 她想调解丈夫和儿子之间的争吵。 4. One town ends where the next begins and there\'s a road that runs between. 一个城镇连接着另一个城镇,两者之间有一条路。', '名词: betweenness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fever', '[\'fiːvər]', 'n.狂热；发烧；发热 v.（使）发烧；（使）狂热', '1. Football fever gripped the town when the local team reached the cup final. 在当地的足球队打进了优胜杯的决赛圈后，全市掀起一阵足球热。 2. War fever was rising all over the Middle East. 战争狂热正在整个中东地区升温。 3. Her fever lasted five days without intermission. 她连续五天一直发烧。 4. My fever is gone, but I still have a cough. 我不发烧了，但还是有点咳嗽。 5. He went to see a doctor at the onset of a fever. 他开始发烧时便去看医生了。', '过去式: fevered 过去分词: fevered 现在分词: fevering 第三人称单数: fevers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('laugh', '[læf]', 'v.发笑；笑；嘲笑 n.笑声；笑；笑料', '1. He could tell she was in a bad mood, and tried to laugh her out of it. 他看出她心情不好，想逗她笑好让她不再想烦恼的事。 2. It is natural to laugh when you are happy. 高兴时笑是正常的。 3. You have to laugh and find humor every day. 每天都要笑，每天都要找到幽默。 4. You should not laugh at the handicapped. 你们不应该嘲笑残疾人。 5. The captain\'s cheerful laugh dispelled our fears. 船长愉快的笑声消除了我们的恐惧。', '副词: laughingly 名词: laugher 过去式: laughed 过去分词: laughed 现在分词: laughing 第三人称单数: laughs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thirsty', '[\'θɜːrsti]', 'adj.口渴的；渴望的', '1. He was thirsty for power. 他渴望拥有权力。 2. The thirsty man craved for water. 那个囗渴的人渴喝水。 3. Young man should be thirsty for knowledge. 青年人应该渴望知识。', '副词: thirstily 比较级: thirstier 最高级: thirstiest 名词: thirstiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stable', '[\'steɪbl]', 'adj.稳定的；安定的；可靠的 n.马棚；马厩；一批人 v.使（马）入厩；入马棚', '1. Markets are flourishing and prices are stable. 市场繁荣, 物价稳定。 2. In order that our country could flourish and achieve its own goals, a stable environment within the country is definitely not dispensable. 国家要发展，要实现自己的目标，这是必不可少的条件，就是要国内有安定的环境。 3. The Sunnis hold a majority in four provinces and any government will have to respect them if they wish to administer a stable state. 逊尼派在四个省份里都是多数群体，而任何政府只要想管理一个安定的国家，就不得不对他们予以尊重。 4. He is a bit neurotic, but his wife is a very stable person. 他有点神经质，但他的妻子是一个非常稳重的人。 5. The horse in the stable has broken out. 马厩里的那匹马跑了。 6. Where do you stable your pony? 你那匹矮种马养在哪儿?（《牛津高阶英汉双解词典》）', '副词: stably 比较级: stabler 最高级: stablest 名词: stableness 过去式: stabled 过去分词: stabled 现在分词: stabling 第三人称单数: stables');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('qualification', '[ˌkwɑːlɪfɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.资格；限制；资历', '1. What sort of qualifications do you need for the job? 做这项工作需要什么资格？ 2. He\'s got all the right qualifications but he is temperamentally unsuitable. 他具备一切合格的条件,惟独性情不适合。 3. The plan was approved without qualification. 这项计划获得无条件批准。 4. I welcome the amendment to the bill without qualification. 我不带任何条件地接受这项法令的修正案。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('locomotive', '[ˌloʊkə\'moʊtɪv]', 'n.火车头；机车 adj.运动的；火车头的；旅行的', '1. He is a locomotive engineer. 他是一名火车司机。 2. They detached the locomotive from the train. 他们使火车头与列车脱离了。 3. The locomotive was dashed to pieces. 机车撞得粉碎。 4. The locomotive pulled a long line of freight cars. 那台机车拖了一长列货车。 5. Hands and feet are locomotive organs. 手和脚是运动器官。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('worth', '[wɜːrθ]', 'n.价值；财富 adj.值得的；值钱的', '1. The thieves stole 1 million pounds\' worth of jewellery. 窃贼偷走了价值100万英磅的珠宝。 2. Just 44 years old, his net worth tops $20 billion. 年仅44岁，他的财富纯价值已高达200亿美元。 3. The movie was definitely worth seeing. 那部电影真的很值得看。 4. Whatever is worth doing at all is worth doing well. 任何值得做的事就值得做好。', '过去式: worthed 过去分词: worthed 现在分词: worthing 第三人称单数: worths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('magnificent', '[mæɡ\'nɪfɪsnt]', 'adj.壮丽的；宏伟的；极好的', '1. The magnificent sights collect a jolly crowd. 壮丽的景色引来欢乐的人群。 2. The Hungarian view is magnificent from the summit of the mountains. 从群山之颠看到的匈牙利景色非常壮丽。 3. Just look at this magnificent autumn landscape! 看看这壮丽的秋景吧！ 4. The Taj Mahal is a magnificent building. 泰姬陵是一座宏伟的建筑。', '副词: magnificently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fairly', '[\'ferli]', 'adv.公正地；相当地', '1. This company deals fairly with every client. 这家公司公正地对待每位客户。 2. I think I was quite fairly treated by the police. 我认为警察对我非常公正。 3. It\'s fairly hot today. 今天相当热。 4. His general state of health is fairly satisfactory. 他总的健康状况相当令人满意。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guarantee', '[ˌɡærən\'tiː]', 'n.保证；保证书；担保；担保人；抵押品 vt.保证；担保', '1. A diploma is no guarantee of efficiency. 持有文凭不能保证工作效率一定高。 2. I guarantee that this will not happen again. 我保证此类事情不会再发生。 3. We guarantee the fastness of these dyes. 我们担保这些染料不褪色。 4. He put up his house as a guarantee. 他提供房子作为担保。 5. A diploma is no guarantee of efficiency. 持有文凭不能保证工作效率一定高。', '过去式: guaranteed 过去分词: guaranteed 现在分词: guaranteeing 第三人称单数: guarantees');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('frontier', '[frʌn\'tɪr]', 'n.边界；边境；尖端；边缘', '1. We were turned back at the frontier. 我们在边界那儿被赶了回来。 2. The frontier ranges from the northern hills to the southern coast. 边界从北部山地一直延伸到南部海岸。 3. Everything is quiet on the frontier. 边境上一切安静。 4. This new frontier incident probably means war. 这个新的边境事件可能导致战争。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('burn', '[bɜːrn]', 'v.燃烧；烧着；烧毁；灼伤；急于 n.烧伤；燃烧', '1. Half the candle had burnt away. 蜡烛已烧去一半。 2. It\'s better to burn out than to fade away! 与其慢慢凋谢,不如灿烂燃烧! 3. Paper burns easily. 纸容易着火。 4. If the satellite returns to earth too fast, it will burn up on the way. 如果人造卫星返回地球太快,它在归途中就会烧毁了。 5. Tell him to put cold water on the burn. 告诉他,在烧伤处敷凉水。', '过去式: burned/burnt 过去分词: burned/burnt 现在分词: burning 第三人称单数: burns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('furnace', '[\'fɜːrnɪs]', 'n.炉子；熔炉；闷热地带；严峻考验', '1. This room is like a furnace. 这屋子热得象火炉一样。 2. Would you please fire the furnace? 你去给炉子添加燃料好吗? 3. The metal glowed in the furnace. 金属在熔炉里发出灼热的光。 4. He endured the furnace of his friends\'blame after the accident. 事故发生之后,他遭朋友指责的考验', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('November', '[noʊ\'vembər]', 'n.十一月', '1. They will get married in November. 他们十一月要结婚。 2. November is the high tourist season for southeast Asia. 十一月是东南亚旅游的旺季。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transcend', '[træn\'send]', 'v.超越；胜过', '1. Humans should always transcend their limits. 人类应该不断超越自己的极限。 2. We can\'t transcend the limitations of the ego. 我们无法超越自我的局限性。 3. They transcend national borders and generations. 它们超越国界及世代。 4. The song of the future must transcend creed. 赞美未来的颂歌一定要胜过这类教条。', '过去式: transcended 过去分词: transcended 现在分词: transcending 第三人称单数: transcends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deliver', '[dɪ\'lɪvər]', 'v.递送；发表（演讲）；交付；解救；生（孩子）；接生；履行；投掷', '1. The mailman delivers letters and parcels every morning. 邮差每天早晨递送信件和包裹。 2. He delivered a long prose. 他发表了一篇冗长乏味的演讲。 3. We deliver the goods in batches. 我们分批交付货物。 4. Education delivered him from ignorance. 教育把他从无知中解救出来。', '形容词: deliverable 名词: deliverability 过去式: delivered 过去分词: delivered 现在分词: delivering 第三人称单数: delivers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('merit', '[\'merɪt]', 'n.优点；功绩；价值 v.值得；应得', '1. This method at least had the merit of simplicity. 这种办法至少有简单明了的优点。 2. Charms strikes the sight, but merit wins the soul. 美貌吸引目光,优点赢得心灵。 3. That will subtract nothing from his merit. 那将无损于他的功绩。 4. Promotion should be based on merit alone. 晋升应完全根据功绩。 5. His new achievements merit our attention. 他取得的新成就值得关注。', '形容词: meritless 过去式: merited 过去分词: merited 现在分词: meriting 第三人称单数: merits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('percentage', '[pər\'sentɪdʒ]', 'n.百分率；比例；部分；好处', '1. The percentage at grade E and above for day school candidates in the HKCEE was 67.5 compared with 65.6 in 1998. 中学会考日校考生报考的科目成绩达E级或以上的有67. 2. What percentage of the earth is covered by oceans? 地球上百分之多少被海水覆盖着？ 3. Whisky contains a large percentage of alcohol. 威士忌所含酒精的百分比很高。 4. The percentage of unskilled workers is small. 非熟练工的比例很小。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rib', '[rɪb]', 'n.肋骨；肋状物 vt.装肋于；用肋状物支撑', '1. How many ribs does a man have? 一个人有几条肋骨？ 2. He broke a rib when he fell off his horse. 他从马上摔下来折断了一根肋骨。 3. God used this rib to make a woman. 上帝用这根肋骨创造了女人。 4. He has broken a rib and the doctor has strapped it up. 他断了一根肋骨，医生已包扎好了。', '过去式: ribbed 过去分词: ribbed 现在分词: ribbing 第三人称单数: ribs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bar', '[bɑːr]', 'n.酒吧；条；横木；栅 vt.禁止；阻挠；闩上；在 ... 设栅栏', '1. There are several bars in the hotel. 这家旅馆里有好几个酒吧。 2. A bar of chocolate is enough to stop his crying. 一条巧克力就可以让他不哭了。 3. There\'s a strong bar on the door. 门上有一个很坚固的闩。 4. There is a burning man hovering in the air over a grille in the Smoldering Corpse Bar. 有一个焚烧中的人，飘浮在冒烟尸体酒吧的铁栅上方。 5. After the bombing, the whole area was barred to the public. 轰炸后，整个地区禁止公众通行。', '过去式: barred 过去分词: barred 现在分词: barring 第三人称单数: bars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('startle', '[\'stɑːrtl]', 'v.（使）吃惊；（使）惊愕 n.吃惊；惊恐', '1. He was startled by the news. 这消息使他大吃一惊。 2. He startled from sleep. 他从睡梦中惊醒起来。 3. The least noise would startle the timid child. 最小的响声也会吓着这个胆小的孩子的。 4. Let\'s hide ourselves behind the door and startle her. 藏在门后面，咱们吓她一下。 5. He gave me a startle. 他吓了我一跳。', '副词: startlingly 名词: startlingness 过去式: startled 过去分词: startled 现在分词: startling 第三人称单数: startles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preparation', '[ˌprepə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.准备；预备；配制', '1. He didn\'t do any preparation for this exam, so he failed. 他考试前没做任何准备，所以不及格。 2. Preparations for the Queen\'s visit are almost complete. 女王访问的筹备工作已基本就绪。 3. The preparation for his cough included camphor. 为医治他的咳嗽而调制的药中包括樟脑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sponsor', '[\'spɑːnsər]', 'n.保证人；赞助者；发起者；主办者 v.发起；赞助；倡议', '1. Your sponsor may assist in organising this insurance. 你的担保人可以帮助你办理此类保险。 2. Mr. Robert Brown was announced as the sponsor. 罗勃特·布朗先生被宣布为赞助人。 3. A wealthy sponsor came to our rescue with a generous donation. 有个富有的赞助人慷慨捐赠来解救我们。 4. Who is the sponsor of the research program? 谁是这个研究项目的发起人? 5. The senator announced that he would sponsor the health care plan. 这位参议员宣布他将发起这一保健计划。', '形容词: sponsorial 名词: sponsorship 过去式: sponsored 过去分词: sponsored 现在分词: sponsoring 第三人称单数: sponsors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tiger', '[\'taɪɡər]', 'n.老虎；凶残之人', '1. The tiger is a representative of the cat family. 老虎是猫科动物的典型。 2. The hunter hurled his spear at the tiger. 猎人用力把他的长矛向虎投去。 3. The tiger dragged its kill into the jungle. 这只老虎拖着它的猎物进了丛林。 4. He moved like a tiger stalking its prey. 他像老虎一样悄悄潜近他的猎物。', '形容词: tigerish');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sheet', '[ʃiːt]', 'n.被单；纸；(薄)片；一片 n.[船]帆脚索 v.铺盖；使成片 adj.片状的', '1. We change the sheet every week. 我们每个星期换一次床单。 2. The doctor wanted us to use the sheet for a shroud. 医生想让我们用床单当裹尸布。 3. He put a fresh sheet in the typewriter. 他把一张纸放进了打字机中。 4. She went as white as a sheet when she heard the news. 她听到这个消息顿时脸色苍白。 5. He jammed the tiller, made the sheet fast and reached under the stern for the club. 他刹住了舵把，系紧帆脚索，伸手到船梢下去拿棍子。 6. A plastic sheet was pegged down over the compost heap to hasten decomposition. 把塑料布铺盖在肥堆上，并用木桩固定好，以加速肥料腐烂。', '过去式: sheeted 过去分词: sheeted 现在分词: sheeting 第三人称单数: sheets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mechanism', '[\'mekənɪzəm]', 'n.机制；原理 n.结构；机构；机械装置', '1. The WTO provides a mechanism for resolving trade disputes. 世贸组织提供了一种解决贸易争端的机制。 2. The acting mechanism of coating mist polycoagulant is introduced. 介绍了漆雾凝聚剂的作用原理及选择漆雾凝聚剂的方法。 3. Analyzing the velocity and acceleration of the follower based on the Assur-group method and the inversion of the mechanism. 以杆组分析方法为基础，结合转化机构原理及凸轮机构的相对速度理论进行从动件的速度和加速度分析。 4. She studied the mechanisms of the body. 她研究身体的结构。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cycle', '[\'saɪkl]', 'n.循环；周期；自行车；摩托车 v.骑自行车；(使)轮转；(使)循环', '1. The seasons of the year make a cycle. 一年四季构成一个循环。 2. The business cycle experienced a sudden down. 商业周期经历了突然的萧条。 3. A cycle of the sun takes a year. 太阳循环周期需要一年。 4. I go to school by cycle every day. 我每天骑自行车上学。 5. I usually cycle home through the park. 我通常骑自行车穿过公园回家。', '名词: cycler 过去式: cycled 过去分词: cycled 现在分词: cycling 第三人称单数: cycles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('infrastructure', '[\'ɪnfrəstrʌktʃər]', 'n.基础；基础设施', '1. We actively press ahead with the infrastructure development plan. 我们积极推进基础建设计划。 2. Our city offer overseas investors services for production aside from infrastructure services. 我市除了向外国投资者提供基础设施外,还提供良好的生产服务设施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('purse', '[pɜːrs]', 'n.钱包；小钱袋；(获奖)奖金 vt.皱起；放进钱包', '1. When did you first miss your purse? 你什么时候发现丢了钱包的? 2. The loss of her purse caused her much inconvenience. 丢失钱包给她带来了诸多不便。 3. This piece of china is beyond my purse. 这件瓷器我买不起。 4. Her purse was stolen when she was on the bus. 她的手袋在公共汽车上被偷了。 5. The sour taste made her purse her lips. 酸味使她皱起嘴唇。', '形容词: purselike 过去式: pursed 过去分词: pursed 现在分词: pursing 第三人称单数: purses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outstanding', '[aʊt\'stændɪŋ]', 'adj.优秀的；突出的；未支付的；未完成的', '1. He was an outstanding student. 他是个优秀的学生。 2. Given the chance, John might have become an outstanding painter. 如果有机会,约翰也许已成为一位杰出的画家了。 3. Two things are outstanding in the creation of the English system of canals. 在创建英国运河体系的过程中,有两件事是非常突出的。 4. 75 per cent of the amount originally borrowed is still outstanding. 最初的借款仍有75%25 未偿还。', '副词: outstandingly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('illiterate', '[ɪ\'lɪtərət]', 'adj.文盲的；无知的 n.文盲', '1. Dr. Andrew Sneddon is particularly excited by what has been found as it gives a unique insight into the lives of the working but illiterate inhabitants of the city. 安德鲁斯内登博士对于发现到的事物感到非常兴奋，因为可以深入的了解到这城市劳动但文盲的居民生活。 2. The lateral elite is literally illiterate. 边上的杰出人物简直是文盲。 3. I can confirm that you are illiterate in English! 我能确定你是个英语文盲！', '副词: illiterately 名词: illiterateness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('magazine', '[\'mæɡəziːn]', 'n.杂志；弹盘；弹药库', '1. This magazine has a large circulation. 这本杂志发行量很大。 2. I was reading a magazine when the phone rang. 电话铃响时我正在看一本杂志。 3. This magazine comes out quarterly. 这种杂志一年发行四期。 4. Lieutenant Hearn fingered the magazine on his carbine. 候恩少尉用手摸了一下卡宾枪的弹盒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('subtle', '[\'sʌtl]', 'adj.微妙的；敏锐的；不明显的；精细的；狡猾的', '1. There were subtle hints in his letter. 他的信中有些微妙的暗示。 2. What meaning will my subtle signal make? 我的微妙信号表达了什么意思? 3. She has a very subtle mind. 她有个很敏锐的头脑。 4. Satire is a high and subtle art. 讽刺是一门崇高而又含蓄的艺术。', '副词: subtly 比较级: subtler 最高级: subtlest 名词: subtleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('annoy', '[ə\'nɔɪ]', 'v.使恼怒；使烦恼；骚扰', '1. We can annoy the enemy by raids. 我们可用袭击骚扰敌人。 2. Some peoples\' daily mission is to annoy you! 一些人的日常使命就是骚扰你！', '过去式: annoyed 过去分词: annoyed 现在分词: annoying 第三人称单数: annoys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shine', '[ʃaɪn]', 'v.照耀；出色；发光；投光于；使发光 n.光泽；光辉；阳光；擦皮鞋（美）；喜欢；鬼把戏（复）', '1. The curtain was suddenly drawn and a bright light shone in. 突然窗帘拉了开来，一道强光照了进来。 2. He shines at golf. 他高尔夫球打得很出色。 3. The sun is shinning brightly. 今天阳光格外明媚。 4. Shine your torch into the drawer. 你用手电筒照一下这抽屉里面。 5. The waxed floor had a good shine. 打蜡地板闪闪发光。', '过去式: shone/shined 过去分词: shone/shined 现在分词: shining 第三人称单数: shines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lad', '[læd]', 'n.少年；小伙子；<口>伙伴', '1. He is just a lad. 他不过是个小青年。 2. He\'s a nice lad, but a bit slow on the draw. 他是个挺不错的小伙子，就是头脑欠灵活。 3. He\'s a nice enough lad, but he doesn\'t seem to have much gumption. 他是个不错的小伙子,但好像没有什么进取心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acre', '[\'eɪkər]', 'n.英亩', '1. The shepherd has penned up the sheep in the four acre field. 牧羊人把羊群围在那块四英亩的土地上。 2. The house has half an acre of lawn. 这座房子有半英亩草坪。 3. We own 100 acres of farmland. 我们拥有一百英亩农田。 4. He ploughed an acre in six hours. 他六小时犁一英亩地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clone', '[kloʊn]', 'n.克隆；无性繁殖；复制品 v.克隆；复制', '1. Above all, we must first clone a panda. 最重要的是我们必须首先克隆一只熊猫。 2. The first clone farm has appeared in New Zealand. 第一家克隆农场在新西兰出现。 3. At the outset they must contain several ramets of every selected clone. 在开始时每个入选无性系必须包括几个无性繁殖后代。 4. Clone is the nonsexually-produced descendants of a single plant or animals. 克隆就是无性繁殖单个的植物或动物后代。 5. The first clone farm has appeared in New Zealand. 第一家克隆农场在新西兰出现。', '形容词: clonal 副词: clonally 名词: cloner 过去式: cloned 过去分词: cloned 现在分词: cloning 第三人称单数: clones');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jaw', '[dʒɔː]', 'n.颚；颌；下巴；钳口；说教 v.喋喋不休；教训', '1. A strong square jaw is a sign of firm character. 强健的方颚是性格坚定的象征。 2. He fell from a ladder, and broke his jaw bone. 他从梯子上掉了下来，摔伤了颌骨。 3. Give him a sock on the jaw! 给他下巴上来一拳！ 4. On hearing the news, his jaw dropped. 听到这个消息，他惊讶得张口结舌。 5. Whenever my wife and her mother get together they jaw away for hours. 每当我妻子和她母亲相聚时，她们总要聊上数小时。', '形容词: jawless 过去式: jawed 过去分词: jawed 现在分词: jawing 第三人称单数: jaws');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('signature', '[\'sɪɡnətʃər]', 'n.签署；书帖；有特征的符号；【计】签名', '1. He traced his signature laboriously. 他吃力地签上自己的名字。 2. Her signature was an illegible scrawl. 她的签字潦草难辩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gear', '[ɡɪr]', 'n.传动装置；齿轮；排挡；工具；装备 v.调整；使适应于；以齿轮连起', '1. Careless use of the clutch may damage the gears. 离合器使用不慎可能损坏传动装置。 2. The gear just would not come unstuck. 齿轮就是松不开来。 3. The car has four forward gear and one reverse gear. 那汽车有四个前进挡和一个倒挡。 4. Lifting electromagnet is a kind of lifting gear. 起重电磁铁是起重工具的一种。 5. Education should be geared to the children\'s needs and abilities. 教育应适应儿童的需要和能力。', '过去式: geared 过去分词: geared 现在分词: gearing 第三人称单数: gears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('degree', '[dɪ\'ɡriː]', 'n.学位；程度；度数', '1. He went down without taking a degree. 他没获得学位就离开了大学。 2. To do this job, you must have a degree in English. 从事这个工作你必须具有英语专业的大学学位。 3. She has also been affected, but to a lesser degree. 她也受到波及，但程度较轻。 4. They cannot be trusted in the slightest degree. 对他们一点也不能相信。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prevalent', '[\'prevələnt]', 'adj.流行的；普遍的', '1. Is malaria still prevalent among the populationhere? 疟疾是否仍为此地居民的多发病? 2. Eye diseases are prevalent in some tropical countries. 在一些热带国家，眼疾很流行。 3. This argument was prevalent at the time. 这是当时流行的论调。 4. The prevalent opinion is in favour of reform. 一般舆论都支持改革。', '副词: prevalently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seven', '[\'sevn]', 'num.七', '1. There are seven continents in the world. 世界上有七大洲。 2. Four multiplied by seven is twenty-eight. 7乘4等于28。 3. I have seven roommates in my university. 上大学时，我有七个室友。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crow', '[kroʊ]', 'n.乌鸦；啼叫；欢叫 v.报晓；啼叫；欢叫；夸口；洋洋自得', '1. The crow is a bird of ill omen. 乌鸦是不祥的预兆。 2. He gets up at the crow of the rooster every day. 他每天鸡鸣即起。 3. It was dawn, and I could hear a cock crowing somewhere. 天亮了,我听到从某处传来雄鸡的报晓声。 4. The rooster flew up to a big rock and began to crow. 公鸡飞上大石头,开始鸣叫。', '过去式: crowed 过去分词: crowed 现在分词: crowing 第三人称单数: crows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('audience', '[\'ɔːdiəns]', 'n.听众；观众；读者；倾听；拥护者；正式会见', '1. The audience was no less than five thousand. 听众有五千人之多。 2. Someone in the audience began to laugh. 观众中有人开始笑起来。 3. The concert drew a large audience. 音乐会吸引了大量的观众。 4. The article was put out in a national magazine to reach a larger audience. 为了能影响更多的读者,文章被登发在一份国家级杂志上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attack', '[ə\'tæk]', 'n.攻击；抨击 v.攻击；抨击；发动攻击；（疾病）侵袭', '1. The police are launching a major attack on drug dealers. 警方对毒品贩子发动了大规模的攻击。 2. His attack on the government was pure vitriol. 他纯粹出于恶意抨击政府。 3. The enemy attacked us at night. 敌人在夜里向我们进攻。 4. There is a newspaper article attacking the Prime Minister. 报纸上有一篇抨击首相的文章.', '名词: attacker 过去式: attacked 过去分词: attacked 现在分词: attacking 第三人称单数: attacks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('baggage', '[\'bæɡɪdʒ]', 'n.行李', '1. Let me put your baggage in the trunk. 我来把你的行李放在汽车后部的行李箱内。 2. Our baggage has cleared customs. 我们的行李已通过海关检查。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consideration', '[kənˌsɪdə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.考虑；体贴；考虑因素；敬重；意见', '1. Please give the matter your careful consideration. 此事请你仔细考虑。 2. He showed no consideration for his wife. 他不体贴他的妻子。 3. Thank you for all your consideration and help. 谢谢您的关心和帮助。 4. Time is an important consideration in this case. 在这种情况下，时间是一个要考虑的重要因素。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('horn', '[hɔːrn]', 'n.喇叭；触角；角质；号 v.强行介入', '1. The driver tooted his horn as he approached the bend. 开车的人在快要转弯时按响了喇叭。 2. The driver hooted his horn (at us). 司机(冲著我们)鸣喇叭。 3. The rhinoceros has one horn on its nose. 犀牛鼻子上有一个角。 4. The lark\'s on the wing, the snail\'s on the horn. 云雀在空中飞翔，蜗牛伸出触角爬行。 5. Although he was not invited,Henry managed to horn in on Myra\'s wedding. 尽管亨利没有被邀请，他还是设法闯来参加迈拉的婚礼。', '名词: hornist 过去式: horned 过去分词: horned 现在分词: horning 第三人称单数: horns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intense', '[ɪn\'tens]', 'adj.强大的；紧张的；强烈的；激烈的；深刻的', '1. He\'s been under intense pressure. 他面对着很大的压力。 2. My work is so intense that I even have no time to take a rest. 我的工作非常紧张，以致于我没有时间休息。 3. Her feelings are so intense as to move the present into tears. 她的感情如此之切,使在场的人都流下了眼泪。 4. There was intense competition between the rival companies to get the contract. 为得到这份合同,各不相让的两家公司展开了激烈的竞争。', '副词: intensely 比较级: intenser 最高级: intensest 名词: intenseness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surround', '[sə\'raʊnd]', 'vt.包围；环绕 n.环绕物', '1. The house was surrounded by high walls. 房子的四周有高墙。 2. They have surrounded the town with troops. 他们出动军队包围了该城。 3. Trees surround the pond. 树木围绕着池塘。 4. This old fireplace has a very attractive surround. 这个老壁炉有个非常引人注目的围绕物。', '过去式: surrounded 过去分词: surrounded 现在分词: surrounding 第三人称单数: surrounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('distribute', '[dɪ\'strɪbjuːt]', 'v.分配；散发；分布', '1. Please distribute books among the students. 把书发给学生。 2. Clothes and blankets have been distributed among the refugees. 向难民分发了衣服和毯子。 3. We distribute handbills on the street every weekend. 我们每周都要在街上散发传单。 4. Some types of plants are widely distributed. 有些植物分布得很广。', '过去式: distributed 过去分词: distributed 现在分词: distributing 第三人称单数: distributes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('parasite', '[\'pærəsaɪt]', 'n.寄生虫；寄生生物；食客', '1. Rupture of the parasite may result in anaphylaxis. 寄生虫的碎裂可能导致过敏反应。 2. These flies carry a dangerous parasite. 这些苍蝇携带一种危险的寄生虫。 3. The parasite\'s host could be any bird. 该寄生生物的宿主可以是任何鸟类。 4. The result is a repeated signal, and a new limb forms in addition to the one to which the parasite attached itself. 这样的结果将是一种持续的讯号，而一种被寄生生物附著在肢体上所产生的新的生长型态将应运而生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('briefcase', '[\'briːfkeɪs]', 'n.公文包', '1. He put all the files into his briefcase. 他将所有文件都装进公文包。 2. No one told me about any briefcase. 没有人和我提过什么公文包。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('survival', '[sər\'vaɪvl]', 'n.幸存；幸存者；生存；残存物，幸存物；【人类学】(失去原有意义、作用的)残存文化特征', '1. Hopes are fading for the survival of the missing climbers. 失踪的登山者幸存的希望越来越渺茫。 2. The miraculous survival of some people in the air crash was widely reported by the press. 空难事件中有些人大难不死被新闻界广泛报导。 3. She is the only survival in the accident. 她是事故中的惟一幸存者。 4. Survival is our first imperative. 我们当务之急是设法生存下来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elevator', '[\'elɪveɪtər]', 'n.<美>电梯；飞机升降舵；斗式皮带输送机', '1. I go up by the elevator. 我搭电梯上去。 2. Her job is to operate an elevator. 她的工作是开电梯。 3. The elevator of an aircraft can make it ascend or descend. 飞机的升降舵可以使它升降自如。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('embed', '[ɪm\'bed]', 'v.(使)插入；(使)嵌入；深留脑中', '1. The harpoon struck but did not embed. 鱼叉击中了但并没有插入。 2. You can embed URLs in your comment lines. 可以将URL嵌入注释行。 3. The scene was embedded in his memory. 那一幕情景深深地留在他的记忆。 4. The idea bacame embedded in his mind. 这想法在他头脑中根深蒂固了。', '异体字: imbed 名词: embedment 过去式: embedded 过去分词: embedded 现在分词: embedding 第三人称单数: embeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('however', '[haʊ\'evər]', 'adv.然而；无论如何；不管多么 conj.不管怎样', '1. She felt ill. She went to work, however, and tried to concentrate. 她病了。然而她照旧去上班，并且尽力集中精神工作。 2. His first response was to say no. Later, however, he changed his mind. 他最初的反应是不同意。可是后来他改变了主意。 3. He will never succeed however hard he tries. 不论他怎样努力,都不会获得成功。 4. You won\'t move that stone, however strong you are. 不管你力气多大,也休想搬动那块石头。 5. However sly a fox may be, it is no match for a good hunter. 狐狸再狡猾也架不住好猎手。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expose', '[ɪk\'spoʊz]', 'vt.揭露；使曝光；使面临；使暴露', '1. The reporter was killed because he tried to expose a plot. 这名记者因为试图揭露一个阴谋而被杀害。 2. I hate the paparazzi.They always expose the people\'s privacy. 我讨厌狗仔队,他们老曝光别人的隐私。 3. We should not expose our children to horrors. 我们不应该让孩子看恐怖片。 4. Keep indoors and don\'t expose your skin to the sun. 待在室内,不要把皮肤暴露在阳光下。', '名词: exposer 过去式: exposed 过去分词: exposed 现在分词: exposing 第三人称单数: exposes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('snake', '[sneɪk]', 'n.蛇；狡诈的人 v.蜿蜒；拖曳', '1. I have a fear of snakes. 我害怕蛇。 2. The snake coiled itself around the tree. 蛇盘绕在树上。 3. The girl screamed at the sight of the snake. 那女孩看到蛇就尖叫起来。 4. He was taken to the hospital to be treated for snake bite. 他因遭蛇咬而被送到医院治疗。 5. The river snaked away into the distance. 那条河蜿蜒曲折流向远方。', '过去式: snaked 过去分词: snaked 现在分词: snaking 第三人称单数: snakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chief', '[tʃiːf]', 'adj.主要的；首要的 n.首领', '1. In USA, NewYork City is the chief seat of commerce. 在美国,纽约是主要的商业中心。 2. What are the chief exports of your country? 你们国家有哪些主要的出口物品？ 3. Slow speed is the chief drawback of sea shipment. 海运最大的缺点是速度慢。 4. The chief interchanged the diamond with some pieces of glass. 那首领拿一些玻璃块替换了那些钻石。', '名词: chiefdom');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('piece', '[piːs]', 'n.件；篇；片；块；作品；碎片 v.修补；拼合，凑合', '1. The book is a fine piece of scholarship. 这部书是一件优秀的学术成果。 2. This is an elegant piece of writing. 这篇东西写得很优美。 3. Would you please give me a piece of paper? 能给我一张纸吗？ 4. I think I can do with one more piece. 我想我还能再吃一块。', '过去式: pieced 过去分词: pieced 现在分词: piecing 第三人称单数: pieces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('merry', '[\'meri]', 'adj.愉快的；欢乐的；<口>微醉的', '1. There is a merry smile on her face. 她脸上露出愉快的微笑。 2. He is in a very merry mood today. 他今天心情极为愉快。 3. Merry Christmas! 圣诞快乐！ 4. He ended his speech with a merry quip. 他以十分风趣的话结束了演讲。', '副词: merrily 比较级: merrier 最高级: merriest 名词: merriness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('manual', '[\'mænjuəl]', 'adj.手工的；体力的 n.指南；手册；键盘', '1. Work done by machines has replaced manual labour. 机器生产已经代替了手工劳作。 2. Making small models requires manual skill. 制作小模型要手巧。 3. Having grown up in the countryside, I\'m used to manual labor. 我生长在农村,习惯体力劳动了。 4. This manual is full of useful tips. 这本小册子里有很多实用的小建议。', '副词: manually');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seize', '[siːz]', 'v.抓住；夺取；利用；没收', '1. Seize the chance, otherwise you\'ll regret it. 抓住这个机会，否则你会后悔的。 2. Before he could run away, she seized him by the collar. 在他逃跑之前,她抓住了他的衣领。 3. In a climate of political unrest, a dictator can often seize power. 在动荡的政治气候下,独裁者常常能夺取政权。 4. He would seize upon any excuse to justify himself. 他会利用任何借口为自己辩解。', '形容词: seizable 名词: seizer 过去式: seized 过去分词: seized 现在分词: seizing 第三人称单数: seizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('opportunity', '[ˌɑːpər\'tuːnəti]', 'n.机会；时机', '1. You must grasp this opportunity. 你必须抓住机会。 2. We should seize the opportunity to counterattack. 现在，我们应乘机反攻。 3. I\'d like to take this opportunity to thank everyone for their hard work on the project. 我愿借此机会感谢每一位为这个项目辛勤工作的人。 4. The opportunity has not yet arrived. 时机尚未成熟。', '名词复数: opportunities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('climate', '[\'klaɪmət]', 'n.气候；风气', '1. Britain has a temperate climate. 英国气候温和。 2. She adapted herself quickly to the new climate. 她很快就适应了这种新气候。 3. The small city has the climate that is changeable in the extreme. 这座小城有变化多端的气候。 4. In the current critical climate her work is not popular. 在当前评论风气影响下，她的作品不怎么受欢迎。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transaction', '[træn\'zækʃn]', 'n.交易；办理；处理；事务 （复）transactions: 学报；会报.', '1. Had you not helped us, we should have canceled this transaction. 假如没有你的帮助，这笔生意早就告吹了。 2. His failure in this transaction was due to nothing else than his own carelessness. 他在这笔交易中的失利完全是由于他自己的粗心大意。 3. Payments by cheque easily outnumbered cash transactions. 用支票付款在数量上大大超过现金交易。 4. They charge a fixed rate for each transaction. 他们对办理的每项业务收取一定的费用。', '形容词: transactional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pregnant', '[\'preɡnənt]', 'adj.怀孕的；充满的；意味深长的', '1. How long has she been pregnant? 她怀孕多久了？ 2. She got pregnant and was turned out of the house by her parents. 她怀孕了，父母把她赶出了家门。 3. Women who do not ovulate regularly have difficulty in becoming pregnant. 妇女排卵期不正常就不易受孕。 4. He is a man pregnant with ideas. 他是一个思想丰富的人。', '副词: pregnantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('X-ray', '[\'eksreɪ]', 'n.X射线；光机；X光照片 vt.用X射线检查', '1. When will I know the result of my x ray? 我何时可以知道X光检查的结果? 2. X ray is increasingly used in industry as well. 在工业中X射线也得到了广泛应用。 3. The x ray show a fractured ankle. X 光片显示足踝骨折。 4. You shall have an x ray examination. 你应该作X光检查。', '过去式: x-rayed/X-rayed 过去分词: x-rayed/X-rayed 现在分词: x-raying/X-raying 第三人称单数: x-rays/X-rays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chest', '[tʃest]', 'n.胸部；胸腔；箱子；金库', '1. The soldier received a serious wound on the chest. 这名士兵胸部受了重伤。 2. The bullet hit him in the chest. 子弹击中了他的胸膛。 3. Chest pains may be symptomatic of heart disease. 胸痛可能是心脏病的症状。 4. The diaphragm is between the chest and the abdomen. 横隔膜位于胸腔与腹部之间。', '形容词: chested');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('agreement', '[ə\'ɡriːmənt]', 'n.同意；一致；协议', '1. We are in agreement with their decision. 我们同意他们的决定。 2. I am in entire agreement with you. 我完全同意你。 3. The teacher nodded in agreement. 老师同意地点点头。 4. We are in substantial agreement. 我们实际上意见一致。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('can', '[kæn]', 'aux.可以；能 n.罐头 v.罐装；<口>解雇', '1. You can count on me. 你可以指望我。 2. How can you say that? 你怎么可以这样说？ 3. I don\'t have a pen. Can yon lend me one? 我没有笔,你能借我一支吗? 4. As long as he comes,the problem can be solved. 只要他来,问题就能解决。', '名词: canner 过去式: canned 过去分词: canned 现在分词: canning 第三人称单数: cans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compute', '[kəm\'pjuːt]', 'v.(用计算机或计数器)计算；估计', '1. Ask the waiter to compute the bill. 请侍者算帐。 2. He failed to compute the interest. 他没有把利息算进去。 3. People appear to be born to compute. 人似乎生来就会计算。 4. We can compute the circular area with radius. 我们能用半径计算出圆的面积。', '形容词: computable 名词: computability 过去式: computed 过去分词: computed 现在分词: computing 第三人称单数: computes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hostess', '[\'hoʊstəs]', 'n.女主人；空姐；女主持', '1. The hostess made her guests comfortable. 女主人使客人们感到舒适自在。 2. The hostess gave us a cordial greeting. 女主人热忱地欢迎我们。 3. You need a lot of tact to be an air hostess. 当空中小姐言行需十分得体。 4. Now that she\'s an air hostess, foreign travel has lost its glamour for her. 她当上了空中小姐，到国外旅行对她已失去吸引力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outing', '[\'aʊtɪŋ]', 'n.郊游；远足；外出', '1. I think we should postpone the outing. 我认为我们应该推迟这次郊游。 2. It is such a fine day for an outing. 今天是这样一个适合于郊游的好日子。 3. We went for an outing on a crisp fall day. 我们在一个秋高气爽的日子去远足了。 4. Our plan for an outing is contingent on the weather. 我们外出游玩的计划视天气而定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glamor', '[\'glæmə]', 'n.魅力；吸引力 =glamour(英).', '1. The glamor with eyes rolling is so charming! 那种眼神流转的魅力实在非常迷人！ 2. What makes television distinctive is its glamor and its reach. 使电视具有特色的东西是它那迷人的魅力以及传播范围之广。 3. As in the sample objectives above, the compelling content might simply be glamor photos of your widgets in use by other people. 上文中提到，有吸引力的内容可以提供其他用户使用产品的照片，这种方法经常被用到。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('less', '[les]', 'adj.更少的；较少的 adv.更少地；较少地 n.少量；次要 prep.减', '1. It would be good to have less pollution. 如果污染更少的话就好了。 2. He spends less time on work than on play. 他在工作上花的时间比在玩上面花的时间更少。 3. It is better to complete the task with less money. 最好是用较少的钱就能完成任务。 4. The flaw in this vase makes it less valuable. 这个花瓶因为有点缺陷，不那么值钱了。 5. There is less to do in this job than the last. 这份工作没有上份工作量大。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('most', '[moʊst]', 'adj.最多的；大多数的 adv.最；最多；极其 pron.大多数；大部分 n.最多', '1. This is the area that attracts the most attention. 这是最受关注的地区。 2. Studying on our own brings the most knowledge. 自己钻研可带来最多的知识。 3. Who do you think will get (the) most votes? 你认为谁会得到最多的选票? 4. Most students passed the examination. 大多数学生通过了考试。 5. What did you most enjoy? 你最欣赏的是什麽? 6. Most of the town was destroyed. 小镇的大部分地区被破坏了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transparent', '[træns\'pærənt]', 'adj.透明的；明显的；清晰的', '1. Plain glass is transparent. 普通的白玻璃是透明的。 2. The insect\'s wings are almost transparent. 这昆虫的翅膀几乎是透明的。 3. It was transparent that her pride was hurt. 很显然，她的自尊心受到了伤害。 4. Your words are a transparent lie. 你所说的明显是谎言。', '副词: transparently 名词: transparentness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stun', '[stʌn]', 'vt.使震惊；使目瞪口呆；使昏迷 n.震惊；晕眩', '1. This speech seemed to stun the king. 这话似乎使国王大吃一惊。 2. He was stunned by the sudden news. 他因听到这突然的消息而目瞪口呆。 3. She sat stunned for a while, until she recovered. 她一时昏迷，坐下呆了一会儿才醒过来。 4. The punch stunned me for a moment. 那一拳把我打得昏了一阵。 5. How do I set a laser printer to stun? 我怎么把一台激光打印机设置到震惊？', '过去式: stunned 过去分词: stunned 现在分词: stunning 第三人称单数: stuns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('speciality', '[ˌspeʃi\'æləti]', 'n.专长', '1. Her speciality is ancient Greek poetry. 她的专长是古希腊诗。 2. His speciality is barbecued steaks. 烤牛排是他的拿手好菜。 3. To make stuffed dumpling is his speciality. 包饺子是他的拿手好戏。 4. Her speciality is medieval history. 她专修中世纪史。', '名词复数: specialities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heritage', '[\'herɪtɪdʒ]', 'n.遗产；继承物', '1. One of the glories of the British heritage is the right to a fair trial. 英国人引以自豪的传统之一是有获得公正审判的权利。 2. A novelist must be able to use the cultural heritage of his nation. 小说家要善于利用他本国的文化遗产。 3. These beautiful old palaces are part of our national heritage. 这些美丽的古老宫殿是我们民族遗产的一部分。 4. It is the heritage of all human beings. 这都是整个人类继承的东西', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('paint', '[peɪnt]', 'v.油漆；绘画 n.油漆；颜料；绘画作品', '1. I personally think we should paint the wall yellow. 我个人认为墙壁应该粉刷成黄色。 2. They painted a coat of paint to prevent the oxidation of the ship by seawater. 他们刷了一层油漆以防止船只被海水氧化。 3. She learns to paint in the fashion of Picasso. 她学着以毕加索的手法(绘画风格)绘画。 4. I suggest you paint on wood instead of paper. 我建议你在木头上画而不是在纸上画。 5. The wall requires a new coat of paint. 这墙需要再涂一层新油漆。', '形容词: paintable 名词: paintability 过去式: painted 过去分词: painted 现在分词: painting 第三人称单数: paints');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('edition', '[ɪ\'dɪʃn]', 'n.版；版本', '1. The second edition greatly improves on the first edition. 第二版比第一版好了许多。 2. It has just entered the seventh edition. 它刚出版了第七版。 3. This edition of the dictionary is sold out. 这个版本的字典已售完了。 4. Have you read the unabridged edition of that book? 你读过那本书的全文版本吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('object', '[\'ɑːbdʒekt]', 'n.物体；目标；对象；宾语 v.反对；提出 ... 作为反对的理由', '1. Various objects were on the table. 桌子上摆着各种各样的物体。 2. His one object in life is to earn as much money as possible. 一生中的他的一个目标将挣得尽可能多的钱。 3. This church is the main object of his interest. 他最感兴趣的是这座教堂。 4. If it is a transitive verb, what is its object? 如果是及物动词,它的宾语是什么? 5. In the final analysis, I object to the proposal. 归根结底,我反对这个建议。', '名词: objector 过去式: objected 过去分词: objected 现在分词: objecting 第三人称单数: objects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invariably', '[ɪn\'veriəbli]', 'adv.不变地；总是；一贯地', '1. We always invariably support him. 我们一如既往地支持他。 2. Invariably I take a nap after lunch. 午饭后，我总是睡个午觉。 3. Wives say that men are invariably children at heart. 妻子们说男人实际上永远是孩子。 4. His intuition is invariably correct. 他的直觉常常是正确的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('paradox', '[\'pærədɑːks]', 'n.悖论；似非而是的论点；自相矛盾的话', '1. The gorilla is something of a paradox in the African scene. 在非洲大舞台上大猩猩有点象似是而非的隽语。 2. This paradox cannot be explained, you have to experience it. 这种悖论是不能解释的，你必须经历它。 3. Paradox and irony are characteristics of her style. 她善於运用似非而是的隽语和反语。 4. `More haste, less speed\' is a well-known paradox. ｀欲速不达＇是人所熟知的隽语。', '形容词: paradoxical 副词: paradoxically 名词: paradoxicalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('collection', '[kə\'lekʃn]', 'n.收集；收取，托收；聚集；收藏品；募捐', '1. The collection of these stamps took ten years. 收集这些邮票花了十年时间。 2. There are two collections a day from this letter box. 这个邮箱每天开两次。 3. Is the collection going to be divided up or sold as a whole? 这批收藏品是零卖还是一起卖? 4. The painting has pride of place in his collection. 这幅画在他的收藏品中最为珍贵', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wool', '[wʊl]', 'n.羊毛；毛线；毛织品', '1. These goats are specially bred for their wool. 这些山羊是专为剪取羊毛而饲养的。 2. He found a job of shearing wool from sheep. 他找到一份剪羊毛的工作。 3. She asked me to wind the wool for her. 她叫我帮她绕毛线。 4. She passed me a skein of wool. 她递给我一绞毛线。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('policy', '[\'pɑːləsi]', 'n.政策；方针 n.保险单', '1. They expressed their dissent from official policy. 他们对官方的政策表示出异议。 2. I will never swerve from my declared policy on this matter. 我决不背离我已经宣布的在这个问题上的政策。 3. This latest incident may be the lever needed to change government policy. 最近的事件或许可以作为迫使政府改变政策所需的手段。 4. This is a constant policy to conduct our steps. 这是指导我们行动的一贯方针。 5. The annual premium on my policy is 3000 yuan. 我的保险单每年的保险费是三千元。', '名词复数: policies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ascertain', '[ˌæsər\'teɪn]', 'vt.确定；查明；探知', '1. I ascertain that he was murdered. 我确定他是被谋杀的。 2. I ascertained the disease to be diphtheria. 我确定该病为白喉。 3. The detective was trying to ascertain exactly who was at the party. 这个侦探试图查明都有谁参加了聚会。 4. I\'m going to ascertain the truth. 我要查明真相。', '形容词: ascertainable 副词: ascertainably 名词: ascertainableness 过去式: ascertained 过去分词: ascertained 现在分词: ascertaining 第三人称单数: ascertains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contaminate', '[kən\'tæməˌneɪt]', 'vt.弄脏；污染', '1. Contaminate your bed, and you will one night suffocate in your own waste. 如果你弄脏了自己的环境，总有一天会窒息在你所丢弃的垃圾之中。 2. All over the world, oil spills regularly contaminate coasts. 在世界各地，油溢出物经常污染着海岸。 3. They are contaminating the minds of our young people with these subversive ideas. 他们这些颠覆性的思想是对我们年轻人的精神污染。', '形容词: contaminative 名词: contaminator 过去式: contaminated 过去分词: contaminated 现在分词: contaminating 第三人称单数: contaminates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loan', '[loʊn]', 'n.贷款；借出 v.借；供应货款', '1. The bank will accommodate him with a loan. 银行将向他提供一笔贷款。 2. I propose to repay the loan at 20 pounds a month. 我打算每月偿还贷款20英镑。 3. She offered me the loan of her car. 她提出把汽车借给我用。 4. I have the book out on loan from the library. 我从图书馆里借出那本书。 5. Can I loan a ladder from you for a day or so? 我可以借你的梯子用一两天吗?', '名词: loaner 过去式: loaned 过去分词: loaned 现在分词: loaning 第三人称单数: loans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('element', '[\'elɪmənt]', 'n.要素；元素；（学科的）基本原则；(复数)恶劣天气；元件', '1. Justice is an important element of good government. 公正是仁政的要素. 2. Honesty, industry and kindness are elements of a good life. 诚实、勤劳和善良是幸福生活的要素。 3. Water is composed of the elements hydrogen and oxygen. 水是由氢元素和氧元素组成的。 4. You must understand the elements of mathematics before we can proceed further. 你必须先弄懂数学基础知识，我们才能进一步学习。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('precede', '[prɪ\'siːd]', 'vt.在 ... 之前；先于 vi.在前面；领先', '1. He precede his speech with a welcome to the guest. 他演讲前先对来宾表示欢迎。 2. He came in, preceded by his wife. 他和他的妻子一前一后地走了进来。 3. The we should always precede the I. 集体总应先于个人。 4. This duty should precede all others. 此项义务应该优先于其他一切义务。 5. The days that preceded were filled with activity. 前几天排满了活动。', '过去式: preceded 过去分词: preceded 现在分词: preceding 第三人称单数: precedes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resemblance', '[rɪ\'zembləns]', 'n.相像；相似', '1. Mary bears a striking resemblance to her sister. 玛丽和她的姐妹极其相像。 2. There was a distant resemblance between them. 他俩有隐约相似的地方。 3. Twins often show great resemblance. 双生子常极相似。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('superiority', '[suːˌpɪri\'ɔːrəti]', 'n.优越性；优势', '1. This is the only way to demonstrate the superiority of socialism. 只有这样，才能表明社会主义的优越性。 2. Socialist democracy enjoys strong vitality and superiority. 社会主义民主政治具有强大的生命力和优越性。 3. Your army has numerical superiority over theirs. 与他们相比你们的军队占有人数优势。 4. He won the bout by great superiority. 他以绝对优势赢了这场比赛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sorrow', '[\'sɑːroʊ]', 'n.悲伤；悲痛；懊悔；伤心事 vi.悲伤；惋惜；悔恨', '1. He wrung his hands in sorrow. 他悲伤地绞紧双手。 2. He hanged himself in sorrow after his wife died. 妻子死后，他因悲伤而自缢。 3. Life has many joys and sorrows. 人生有许多欢乐和悲伤。 4. At last she keened her sorrow to me. 终于她向我哭诉了悲痛之情。 5. We sorrow over the death of his son. 我们都为他儿子死感到悲伤。', '名词: sorrower 过去式: sorrowed 过去分词: sorrowed 现在分词: sorrowing 第三人称单数: sorrows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prevail', '[prɪ\'veɪl]', 'vi.盛行；获胜；劝说', '1. This old custom does not prevail now. 这种旧风俗现在已经不流行了。 2. Misty weather prevails in this part of the country. 该国的这一地区天气多雾。 3. Virtue will prevail against evil. 美德定将战胜邪恶。 4. I tried to prevail on him to stay. 我曾试图说服他留下。', '名词: prevailer 过去式: prevailed 过去分词: prevailed 现在分词: prevailing 第三人称单数: prevails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deprive', '[dɪ\'praɪv]', 'vt.剥夺；失去；免职', '1. We have no right to deprive their life. 我们没有权利去剥夺它们的生命。 2. The spread of television have considerably deprive us of our time for reading. 电视的普及剥夺了我们相当多的阅读时间。 3. You can\'t deprive her of her rights. 你不能剥夺她的权利。 4. These trees deprive my house of light. 这些树遮住了我房屋的光线。', '形容词: deprivable 过去式: deprived 过去分词: deprived 现在分词: depriving 第三人称单数: deprives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('furious', '[\'fjʊriəs]', 'adj.狂怒的；猛烈的', '1. I was annoyed, indeed furious, over what happened. 出了这件事我很不痛快,实际上是愤怒至极。 2. If this news ever reaches her ears, she\'ll be furious. 这个消息万一传到她的耳朵里，她一定得大发雷霆。 3. She maintained a calm exterior, though really she was furious. 在外表上她保持着平静，但实际上她生气极了。 4. After receiving the insulting letter, he became furious. 他收到辱骂信后怒不可遏。', '副词: furiously');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refresh', '[rɪ\'freʃ]', 'v.（使）恢复精神；提神；提醒', '1. A cool drink refreshed me after my long walk. 走了很长的一段路之后，一杯冷饮使我恢复了精神。 2. He has drunk one cup of coffee to refresh oneself. 他喝了一杯咖啡提神。 3. I refreshed myself with a cup of coffee. 我喝了一杯咖啡给自己提提神。 4. Let me refresh your memory with some fact. 我来提几件事帮你恢复记忆吧。', '过去式: refreshed 过去分词: refreshed 现在分词: refreshing 第三人称单数: refreshes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('family', '[\'fæməli]', 'n.家庭；亲属；家族；子女；[生]科；语族；[化]族 adj.家庭的；家族的；适合于全家的', '1. There are five people in my family. 我家里有五口人。 2. He was born in a wealthy family. 他出生在一个富裕的家庭。 3. He had to work hard to support his family. 他不得不努力工作来养家。 4. All our family came to Grandad\'s eightieth birthday party. 我们所有的亲属都来参加了祖父八十寿宴。 5. Quarrels are a normal part of family life. 争吵是家庭生活正常的一部分。', '名词复数: families');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('borrow', '[\'bɑːroʊ]', 'v.借；借鉴；抄袭', '1. He uses his house as security to borrow the money. 他用房子作借钱的抵押。 2. May I borrow your roller skates? 我可以借你的旱冰鞋吗？ 3. You can borrow this dictionary from the library. 你可以从图书馆借到这本字典。 4. Handel borrowed music from other composers. 韩德尔的作品借鉴了其他作曲家的乐曲.', '名词: borrower 过去式: borrowed 过去分词: borrowed 现在分词: borrowing 第三人称单数: borrows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whip', '[wɪp]', 'n.鞭子；鞭打；鞭状物 v.抽打；彻底打败', '1. The whip swished through the air. 鞭子嗖地一声在空中挥动。 2. He cracked his whip and the horses began to trot. 他噼噼啪啪地挥鞭策马狂跑。 3. The cruel master beat his slaves with a whip. 残酷的主人鞭打他的奴隶。 4. He was given 30 lashes of the whip. 他被鞭打三十下。 5. The colt used to whip seamen had disappeared on the ship. 船上用来鞭打水手的笞绳不见了。', '名词: whipper 过去式: whipped/whipt 过去分词: whipped/whipt 现在分词: whipping 第三人称单数: whips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('butterfly', '[\'bʌtərflaɪ]', 'n.蝴蝶；蝶状物；蝶泳 vt.(烹饪时把鱼肉等）切开摊平', '1. A butterfly must not be confused with a moth. 不得将蝴蝶和飞蛾混同起来。 2. A caterpillar is the larva of a butterfly. 毛虫是蝴蝶的幼体。 3. A butterfly is flying up and down among the flowers. 有一只蝴蝶正在花丛里忽上忽下地飞着。 4. What are the elements of the butterfly stroke? 蝶泳的泳姿动作要领是什么? 5. Turn the fish over and butterfly it, before you put it in the oven. 把鱼翻过来，切开、摊平，然后放到炉子上。', '过去式: butterflied 过去分词: butterflied 现在分词: butterflying 第三人称单数: butterflies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pleasure', '[\'pleʒər]', 'n.愉快；高兴；快事；（用于回答对方的感谢）荣幸 vt.使高兴 vi.高兴；享受快乐', '1. She took no pleasure in her work. 她觉得自己的工作毫无乐趣。 2. I will remember this meeting with pleasure. 我会愉快地记着这次的会晤。 3. She seemed to take pleasure in our suffering. 她似乎对我们的痛苦幸灾乐祸。 4. It is a pleasure to work with you. 和你一起工作真是件乐事。 5. I really don\'t know how to pleasure him. 我真不知道如何让他高兴。 6. I pleasure in your company. 和你在一起我感到高兴。', '形容词: pleasureless 过去式: pleasured 过去分词: pleasured 现在分词: pleasuring 第三人称单数: pleasures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consultant', '[kən\'sʌltənt]', 'n.顾问；咨询者；<英>会诊医生', '1. Of all the consultants, only Mr. Wang gave us some proposals in point. 所有的顾问当中，只有王先生提了一些中肯的建议。 2. The spy\'s cover was that she was a consultant engineer. 那女间谍伪装成顾问工程师。 3. The consultant was a woman who had many unanswered questions. 这个女性咨询者有许多有待解决的问题。', '名词: consultantship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('husband', '[\'hʌzbənd]', 'n.丈夫', '1. My husband is a stamp collector. 我丈夫是个集邮者。 2. Mary accused her husband of snore too loudly. 玛丽指责她丈夫打呼噜太响。', '过去式: husbanded 过去分词: husbanded 现在分词: husbanding 第三人称单数: husbands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('monkey', '[\'mʌŋki]', 'n.猴子；猴一样的人 v.嘲弄；胡闹；模仿', '1. When the tree falls, the monkeys scatter. 树倒猢狲散。 2. He\'s as mischievous as a monkey! 他像猴子那麽顽皮！ 3. It is dangerous to monkey around in the workshop. 在车间里胡闹是危险的。 4. Don\'t monkey about with this computer. 不要乱动这台计算机。', '名词复数: monkeys 过去式: monkeyed 过去分词: monkeyed 现在分词: monkeying 第三人称单数: monkeys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shuttle', '[\'ʃʌtl]', 'n.梭子；穿梭；往返移动之物；航天飞机 v.往返运送；穿梭移动', '1. The shuttle flies back and forth on the loom. 织布机上梭子来回飞动。 2. He refined the whole art of shuttle diplomacy. 他把穿梭外交艺术提高到炉火纯青的地步。 3. There is a shuttle service between the city center and the air station. 在市中心和飞机场之间有往返的穿梭运行班车。 4. The U.S. made the first space shuttle in the world. 美国制造了世界上第一架航天飞机。 5. We shuttled the passengers to the city center by helicopter. 我们来来回回地用直升机把旅客运送到市中心。', '名词: shuttler 过去式: shuttled 过去分词: shuttled 现在分词: shuttling 第三人称单数: shuttles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pedestrian', '[pə\'destriən]', 'adj.徒步的；缺乏想像的 n.行人', '1. We enjoy all pedestrian activities. 我们喜欢所有的步行活动。 2. They ought to stop at the pedestrian crossing. 他们该停在人行横道上。 3. He was rather a pedestrian student. 他原是个相当平常的学生。 4. We present this approach in a pedestrian version. 我们用平铺直叙的方式介绍这个方法。 5. The driver was slanging a pedestrian who had got in his way. 那司机破口大骂挡他的路的行人。', '名词: pedestrianism');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nineteen', '[ˌnaɪn\'tiːn]', '十九', '1. He lived in Shanghai until he was nineteen. 他在上海一直住到十九岁。 2. The little wretch is only nineteen. 那个小坏蛋还只有十九岁。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wise', '[waɪz]', 'adj.聪明的；有智慧的；明智的；有见识的', '1. Learned men are not necessarily wise. 博学者未必都是聪明的。 2. To a wise person, time is like a diamond. 时间对一个有智慧的人而言，就如钻石般珍贵。 3. A wise general can gain the upper hand in any battle. 一位有智慧的将军在任何战争中都能占上风。 4. She is wise in money matters. 她善于理财。', '副词: wisely 比较级: wiser 最高级: wisest 名词: wiseness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('durable', '[\'dʊrəbl]', 'adj.耐用持久的', '1. It\'s very durable. 这很耐久。 2. This pair of shoes is durable. 这双鞋很耐磨。 3. It calls for a durable solution in the area. 在该地区需要一个持久的解决方法。 4. Our products have the quality of being durable. 我们的产品经久耐用。', '副词: durably 名词: durability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rob', '[rɑːb]', 'v.抢劫；掠夺', '1. Not only do they rob you, they smash everything too. 他们不仅抢夺你的财物，还要把每样东西都捣毁。 2. The robber in arms wanted to rob the bank. 这个持械的强盗想抢劫银行。 3. Ah, I know, it is your desire to rob me of all my gains. I will not disappoint you! 我知道,你想掠夺我的一切获得。我必不使你失望!', '名词: robber 过去式: robbed 过去分词: robbed 现在分词: robbing 第三人称单数: robs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jewel', '[\'dʒuːəl]', 'n.宝石；受珍视的人或物', '1. He examined the jewel with minuteness. 他仔细地检视宝石。 2. The jewel has a beautiful shimmer. 那颗宝石有美丽的闪光。 3. Just feel the weight of this jewel. 把这颗宝石拿在手看看它有多重。 4. A jewel fell off her ring and she could find neither hide nor hair of it. 一颗宝石从她的戒指上脱落了，她四下找，却杳无踪迹。', '过去式: jeweled/jewelled 过去分词: jeweled/jewelled 现在分词: jeweling/jewelling 第三人称单数: jewels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('install', '[ɪn\'stɔːl]', 'vt.安装；安置；使 ... 就职', '1. She installed her air-conditioner without help by herself. 她自己安装了空调。 2. The workers are installing a heating system. 工人们正在安装供暖系统。 3. It is necessary that you install a burglar alarm. 你有必要装防盗警报器。 4. The children are comfortably installed in a new home. 孩子们在新居舒适地安顿下来。', '名词: installer');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weekend', '[\'wiːkend]', 'n.周末 vi.过周末 adj.周末的', '1. How was your weekend? 你周末过得怎么样？ 2. What are your plans for the weekend? 你周末计划做什么？ 3. I weekend with the Whites at their home. 我在怀特家里与他们一家人共度周末。 4. There are more and more weekend couples in the cities. 城市里的周末夫妻越来越多。', '过去式: weekended 过去分词: weekended 现在分词: weekending 第三人称单数: weekends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stupid', '[\'stuːpɪd]', 'adj.愚蠢的；笨拙的；无聊的；乏味的 n.傻瓜', '1. What a stupid idiot! 真是个愚蠢的白痴！ 2. I think he was born stupid. 我认为他生来就愚笨。 3. The woman is proverbially stupid. 这个女人是出名的愚蠢。 4. It was stupid of you to get involved. 你卷进去了，真是愚蠢。 5. Hey, stupid! What do you think you\'re doing! 喂,傻瓜！你以为你在做什么啊！', '副词: stupidly 比较级: stupider 最高级: stupidest 名词: stupidness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('liability', '[ˌlaɪə\'bɪləti]', 'n.责任；债务；倾向；可能性；不利因素', '1. He admitted his liability for the accident. 他承认自己对这起事故应负责任。 2. The judge exempted them from all liability in these matters. 法官免除了他们在这些事上的所有责任和义务。 3. If your liabilities exceed your assets, you may go bankrupt. 如果你所负的债超过你的资产，你就会破产。 4. But the court ruled in favour of Wilson Parking due to a liability disclaimer printed at the entrance. 但法院统治了倾向于威尔逊停放由于责任声明列印在入口。', '名词复数: liabilities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('synthesis', '[\'sɪnθəsɪs]', 'n.合成；综合；综合分析', '1. The ribosome is the site of protein synthesis. 核糖体是合成蛋白质的地方。 2. His work is a synthesis of several ideas. 他的作品是由几种构想综合而成的。 3. Our beliefs are a synthesis of Eastern and Western religions. 我们的信仰是东西方宗教的综合体。 4. We made a synthesis of their studies. 我们综合分析了他们的研究报告。', '名词: synthesist 名词复数: syntheses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('curve', '[kɜːrv]', 'n.曲线；弯曲；弯曲物；弧线', '1. His plane swooped a beautiful curve up and down. 他的飞机在上下翻飞时画出了一条美丽的曲线。 2. The stairs ascended in a graceful curve. 楼梯以优美的曲线上升。 3. His spine developed a slight curve. 他的脊柱有点弯曲。 4. The car made a sharp curve. 汽车拐了一个急弯。', '形容词: curvy 名词: curvedness 过去式: curved 过去分词: curved 现在分词: curving 第三人称单数: curves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arm', '[ɑːrm]', 'n.臂；扶手；袖子 n.武器；军种 vt.武装；装备 （复）arms: 军事行动；纹章；兵役.', '1. You should wind a cloth round the wounded arm. 你应该把一块布缠在受伤的和臂上。 2. The archer holds the bow in his bow arm. 运动员用执弓臂握住弓。 3. His left arm was hurt in an accident. 他的左胳膊在一次事故中受伤了。 4. He draped his legs over the arm of the chair. 他懒洋洋地把双腿搭在椅子的扶手上。 5. They were not allowed to use arms. 不许他们使用武器。 6. We must arm ourselves against the enemy. 我们必须武装自己,防范敌人。', '名词: armer 过去式: armed 过去分词: armed 现在分词: arming 第三人称单数: arms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('absence', '[\'æbsəns]', 'n.缺席；缺乏', '1. His long absence raised fears about his safety. 他长期不在引起了大家对他的安全的担心。 2. What was the real reason for your absence? 你缺席的真正原因是什么？ 3. We are in the absence of experience. 我们缺乏经验。 4. The absence of color in that drawing make it dull. 那幅画因没有着色而显得晦暗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('she', '[ʃi:]', 'pron.她（主格）', '1. She weighs 50 kilograms. 她的体重有50公斤。 2. She can speak Japanese as well as English. 她会说日语和英语。 3. She has served the family faithfully for thirty years. 她为这个家忠心耿耿地操劳了30年。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wood', '[wʊd]', 'n.木材；木头；树林', '1. Our wood supply proved insufficient. 我们的木材供应证明是不够的。 2. We can use plastics in place of wood or metal. 我们可用塑料来代替木材或金属。 3. The man cleft a block of wood in two with an ax. 那人用斧头把一块木头劈成两半。 4. Pine is a soft wood and teak is a hard wood. 松木是软木，柚木是硬木。', '过去式: wooded 过去分词: wooded 现在分词: wooding 第三人称单数: woods');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('matter', '[\'mætər]', 'n.事情；事态；问题；关于...的事情；物质；重要性 v.有关系；要紧', '1. I don\'t talk with my boss about my private matters. 我不和我的老板谈私事。 2. She reluctantly agreed to let the matter drop. 她勉强同意这事到此为止。 3. He reconsidered his decision for the new development of the matter. 他根据事态的发展重新考虑自已的决定. 4. Is anything the matter? 有什么问题吗？ 5. Does it matter what you do next ? 你下一步所做的事关系重大吗?', '过去式: mattered 过去分词: mattered 现在分词: mattering 第三人称单数: matters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cling', '[klɪŋ]', 'vi.紧贴；附着；依恋；坚持 n.紧抓；紧贴', '1. The wet clothes clung to his body. 湿衣服紧贴在他身上。 2. He clung to my arm. 他紧抓着我的胳膊。 3. The cat tried to cling to the edge by its claws. 猫用爪子拼命抓住那边缘。 4. Little children always cling to their mothers. 小孩子总是紧依着母亲。 5. The droid used his magnetized rollers to cling tenaciously to the chromed surface of the ship while deadly turbolaser blasts rained overhead. 在致命的雷射光炮不停地打落在太空船上时，他用具有磁性的滚轮紧抓住舰艇铬制的表面。', '形容词: clingy 名词: clinger 过去式: clung 过去分词: clung 现在分词: clinging 第三人称单数: clings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('horror', '[\'hɔːrər]', 'n.恐怖；战栗；厌恶；震惊 adj.恐怖的', '1. He was filled with horror at the bad news. 听到这个坏消息，他心里充满恐怖。 2. At the sight of the snake, he drew back in horror. 一瞧见那蛇，他便吓得缩了回来。 3. Her eyes were popping out with horror. 她吓得眼睛都瞪圆了。 4. The news struck him with horror. 那消息使他震惊。 5. That horror film made my blood run cold. 那部恐怖影片使我毛骨悚然。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('advantage', '[əd\'væntɪdʒ]', 'n.优势；有利条件 vt.有利于', '1. For a goalkeeper,it\'s a great advantage to have big hands. 对于守门员来说,有一双大手是很大的优势。 2. Rich has an advantage over you since he can speak German. 理奇比你占优势，因为他会讲德语。 3. It is an advantage if you know how to type. 如果你会打字,对你将有利。 4. We should take advantage of all educational opportunities. 我们应该利用一切教育的机会。 5. Such action will advantage our cause. 这样的行动有益于我们的事业。', '过去式: advantaged 过去分词: advantaged 现在分词: advantaging 第三人称单数: advantages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grease', '[ɡriːs]', 'n.油脂 vt.用油脂涂；上油；贿赂', '1. Mother smeared grease on her hands. 母亲用油脂涂沫了双手。 2. The engine was covered in grease. 发动机上有层油脂。 3. I use the floor cleaner to remove grease. 我用地板除垢剂清除油污。 4. You\'re supposed to grease the pan first. 你应该先往锅里加点儿油。', '形容词: greaseless 过去式: greased 过去分词: greased 现在分词: greasing 第三人称单数: greases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('squeeze', '[skwiːz]', 'v.挤压；塞进；压榨；设法腾出 n.挤压；少量；拥挤；严控；财政困难', '1. Kara squeezed the bottle, and the water rushed out. 卡拉挤压着那个瓶子,水一下子喷了出来。 2. It took some ingenuity to squeeze all the furniture into the little room. 把全部家具都塞进那个小房间是很费了一番心思的。 3. Supermarkets are accused of squeezing both customers and suppliers. 超市因压榨顾客和供货商而遭到指控。 4. I can squeeze a meeting in early tomorrow morning. 我可以在明天清早挤出时间开个会。 5. He gave my hand a gentle squeeze. 他握着我的手,轻轻捏了捏。', '形容词: squeezable 名词: squeezer 过去式: squeezed 过去分词: squeezed 现在分词: squeezing 第三人称单数: squeezes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rarely', '[\'rerli]', 'adv.很少；难得', '1. She rarely went anywhere except to her office. 她除了去办公室以外, 很少去别的地方。 2. Rarely did he fail to keep his promise. 他真的很难得失信。 3. Rarely have I seen such a scene. 我难得看到这样的场面。 4. You shouldn\'t miss the opportunity to see the play-it\'s rarely put on. 你不要错过看那出戏的机会,它可是难得上演。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bias', '[\'baɪəs]', 'n.偏见；偏爱；斜纹 vt.使偏心', '1. He has a bias against Japanese products. 他讨厌日本的产品。 2. Histories are often warped by bias. 历史常为偏见所曲解。 3. The judge dispenses the law without bias. 这名法官执法公正无私。 4. Her scientific bias showed itself in early childhood. 她在科学方面的倾向性在孩童时代就已显现出来。 5. The lawyer made a tearful plea to bias the jury. 这名律师以哭诉影响陪审团的裁决。', '过去式: biased/biassed 过去分词: biased/biassed 现在分词: biasing/biassing 第三人称单数: biases/biasses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('incur', '[ɪn\'kɜːr]', 'vt.招致；遭受；惹起', '1. Your despite at him will incur his revenge. 他会因你的藐视态度而报复你的。 2. If you don\'t do the job properly, you will incur blame. 如果你不把工作做好,你将会招人责难。 3. A slowdown in the economy caused us to incur great losses. 经济的减缓使我们遭受了很大的损失。 4. He incurred substantial losses during the stock market crash. 他在股市猛跌时蒙受了巨大的损失。', '过去式: incurred 过去分词: incurred 现在分词: incurring 第三人称单数: incurs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peep', '[piːp]', 'n.瞥见；偷看；初现 n.吱吱叫 v.窥视；慢慢露出 v.吱吱叫', '1. You\'ve only seen a peep through the curtain. 你还只是隔着帘子瞥见一眼罢了。 2. He took a peep at the back of the book to find out the answers to the questions. 他偷偷看了一下书的后面，想找出那些问题的答案。 3. You must start at the peep of dawn. 你们必须在黎明时分动身。 4. The little chicks began to peep because they were hungry. 小鸡因为饿而开始吱吱叫。 5. He squatted down to peep into the basket. 他蹲下来向篮子里窥视了一下。 6. The little chicks began to peep because they were hungry. 小鸡因为饿而开始吱吱叫。', '过去式: peeped 过去分词: peeped 现在分词: peeping 第三人称单数: peeps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dream', '[driːm]', 'n.梦；梦想 v.做梦；梦想', '1. I had some very strange dreams last night. 昨晚我做了很奇怪的梦。 2. I have a recurrent dream that I\'ve turned into an elephant. 我屡次梦见自己变成了大象。 3. My son\'s dream is to be an astronaut. 我儿子的理想是当宇航员。 4. His dream of becoming an artist has been fulfilled. 他成为一个艺术家的梦想实现了。 5. She claims she never dreams. 她说她从来不做梦。', '过去式: dreamed/dreamt 过去分词: dreamed/dreamt 现在分词: dreaming 第三人称单数: dreams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dentist', '[\'dentɪst]', 'n.牙科医生', '1. The dentist told the boy not to eat too many sweets. 牙医告诫这男孩不要吃太多糖果。 2. I have an appointment with my dentist this afternoon. 我已约好今天下午去看牙医。 3. The dentist took out his bad tooth yesterday. 昨天医生拔掉了他的一颗坏牙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fulfill', '[fʊl\'fɪl]', 'vt.完成；履行；执行；满足', '1. Whatever happens I\'m determined to fulfill it. 不管发生什么,我都决心完成它。 2. How they laid about them to fulfill the task! 他们是何等竭尽全力来完成这一任务啊！ 3. You must fulfill your promise. 你必须履行诺言。 4. The doctor\'s instructions must be fulfilled exactly. 必须一丝不苟地遵照医嘱去办。', '名词: fulfiller');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('school', '[skuːl]', 'n.学校；学派；院系；鱼群 v.教育；训练；成群地游', '1. She studies in a high school. 她在一所中学学习。 2. Soon, the whole school knew about her win. 不久，全校师生都知道她获胜了。 3. This is the argument of the school. 这就是流行学派的论据。 4. The Prague School has three important points. 布拉格学派有三个至为重要的观点。 5. She should be schooled with her peers. 她应当与她的同龄人一起接受教育。', '过去式: schooled 过去分词: schooled 现在分词: schooling 第三人称单数: schools');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('damn', '[dæm]', 'int.该死；讨厌 vt.使失败；诅咒；批评 vi.诅咒 n.诅咒；丝毫 adj.该死的；可恶的 adv.非常；极其', '1. Damn! I\'ve broken one of my nails. 该死！我弄断了一个指甲。 2. I made the damn doctors tell me. 我让那些讨厌的医生告诉了我。 3. Oh, damn the dirty swine to hell. 让那卑鄙的畜生见鬼去吧。 4. The book was damned by the critics. 这本书受到批评家的指责。 5. I don\'t give a damn. 我一点也不在乎。 6. \"Week in and week out, we had to write that damn paper.\" 我们都要写那该死的文章。 7. You know damn well what I mean. 你非常明白我的意思。', '副词: damningly 过去式: damned 过去分词: damned 现在分词: damning 第三人称单数: damns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aerial', '[\'eriəl]', 'adj.空中的；空气的；航空的；空想的 n.天线', '1. He showed me some aerial photographs. 他给我看了一些空中拍摄的照片。 2. Aerial pollution is a problem that should be solved quickly. 空气污染是一个亟待解决的问题。 3. Airline is the service industry that offers the aerial affair of transport service. 航空公司属于提供航空运输业务的服务行业。 4. The birds perched on the television aerial. 鸟停在电视天线上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fabricate', '[\'fæbrɪkeɪt]', 'v.编造；虚构；制造', '1. The defense accused police of fabricating evidence. 被告指责警察编造证据。 2. The story was fabricated and completely untrue. 这故事是捏造的，一点不真实。 3. It is not easy to fabricate DNA evidence. 要假造染色体为证是不容易的。 4. The finest crafts people fabricated this golden ring. 这枚金戒指是由最优秀的工匠制作的。', '名词: fabrication 过去式: fabricated 过去分词: fabricated 现在分词: fabricating 第三人称单数: fabricates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appliance', '[ə\'plaɪəns]', 'n.器具；应用；装置；器械', '1. The appliance carries a full-year guarantee. 器具有一年的保证期。 2. These appliances are made of stainless iron. 这些器具是用不锈钢制成的。 3. The appliance of electricity to household task makes housework much easier. 电力应用于家务上使做家务事容易多了。 4. You\'d better not install the appliance in a confined space. 你最好不要把装置安装在密闭的地方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('curious', '[\'kjʊriəs]', 'adj.好奇的；奇特的', '1. I am curious how she will receive the news. 我很想知道她如何接受那消息。 2. The boy was curious about everything he saw. 那男孩对所见的一切都感到好奇。 3. I caught a curious sound in the neighboring room. 我听到隔壁房间里有奇怪的响声。 4. It\'s curious that he didn\'t tell you. 他没有告诉你，实在反常。', '副词: curiously 名词: curiousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weird', '[wɪrd]', 'adj.离奇的；古怪的；怪异的 n.命运；预言者', '1. He looks like nothing on earth in those weird clothes. 他穿著奇装异服难看极了。 2. Jane, I found that guy somewhat weird. 珍妮, 我发觉那家伙有点古怪。 3. That was really a weird movie. 那部电影真怪异! 4. I heard weird shrieks in the darkness. 我在黑暗中听到奇怪的尖叫声。', '副词: weirdly 比较级: weirder 最高级: weirdest 名词: weirdness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cathedral', '[kə\'θiːdrəl]', 'n.大教堂', '1. Photography is strictly forbidden in the cathedral. 教堂内严禁摄影。 2. This street offers a fine vista of the cathedral. 这条街的尽头是个大教堂，远远望去非常好看。 3. The dome of St. Paul Cathedral is well known in the world. 圣保罗教堂的圆顶闻名于世。 4. This cathedral was regarded as a miracle in architectural history. 这座大教堂被认为是建筑史上的奇迹。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('supersonic', '[ˌsuːpər\'sɑːnɪk]', 'adj.超声波的；超音速的 n.超声波；超音速（飞机）', '1. What is classics esophagus supersonic and enchanted graph examination? 什么是经食管超声心动图检查? 2. Have you taken supersonic aircraft? 你坐过超音速飞机吗? 3. These planes travel at supersonic speeds. 这些飞机以超音速的速度飞行。', '副词: supersonically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conspiracy', '[kən\'spɪrəsɪ]', 'n.阴谋；共谋', '1. He is a party to the conspiracy. 他参与了那次阴谋。 2. He revealed their conspiracy to overthrow the government. 他泄露了他们推翻政府的阴谋。 3. It has recently come to light that a second official was implicated in the conspiracy. 最近有消息披露：又有一名高级官员与这个阴谋有牵连。 4. She was convicted on an indictment for conspiracy. 她被控以共谋罪，罪名成立。', '名词复数: conspiracies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('calm', '[kɑːm]', 'adj.平静的；冷静的 v.(使)平静；(使)镇静 n.镇定；平静；平稳', '1. The calm sea gave no hint of the storm that was coming. 平静的海上没有一点迹象显示暴风雨即将来临。 2. She always remains cool, calm and collected in a crisis. 她在危难中总能保持冷静、 平静和镇静。 3. You should keep calm even in face of danger. 即使面临危险，你也应当保持镇静。 4. Moved by what she said, he could hardly calm down. 由于被她那些话所感动,他很难平静下来。 5. Under his apparent calm lay real anxiety. 他表面镇静,内心焦虑。', '副词: calmly 比较级: calmer 最高级: calmest 名词: calmness 过去式: calmed 过去分词: calmed 现在分词: calming 第三人称单数: calms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('golden', '[\'ɡoʊldən]', 'adj.金的；金色的；珍贵的；黄金般的；绝佳的', '1. The best archer would be awarded a golden arrow. 最优秀的弓箭手将获得一只金箭。 2. My parents are celebrating their golden jubilee. 我父母正在庆祝他们的金婚纪念。 3. Her hair has a beautiful golden sheen. 她的头发有美丽的金色的光泽。 4. The road looks beautiful covered by golden pine needles. 这条路上铺满了金黄色的松针，看上去美极了。', '副词: goldenly 名词: goldenness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scent', '[sent]', 'n.气味；香味；线索 v.闻出；发觉；充满；得到 ... 的暗示', '1. The dog easily picked up the scent of the murderer. 狗毫不费力地嗅出了谋杀者的气味。 2. The scent was of leaves and turned earth. 这是树叶和新翻泥土的气味。 3. Through the window I caught the scent of syringa. 从窗口我闻到紫丁香的香味。 4. His nostrils dilated with the scent of the air. 他的鼻孔因为空气中的香味而张大了。 5. The dog scented a rat. 那狗嗅出有老鼠的气味。', '形容词: scentless 过去式: scented 过去分词: scented 现在分词: scenting 第三人称单数: scents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trick', '[trɪk]', 'n.诡计；花招；把戏；诀窍 vt.欺骗；戏弄 adj.有诡计的；有阴谋的', '1. Her tears were just a trick to deceive others. 她的眼泪只是欺骗别人的诡计。 2. You can\'t fool me with that old trick! 你玩弄那种老花招骗不了我! 3. If you watch carefully,you\'ll see how the trick is done. 如果你仔细观看,你就会发现那个把戏是怎么耍的。 4. The trick is to hold your breath while you aim. 窍门就在于瞄准时须屏住呼吸。 5. Her partner tried to trick her out of her share. 她的合伙人企图骗走她的股份。 6. This man is quite trick and undependable. 这个人滑头滑脑，很不可靠。', '名词: tricker 过去式: tricked 过去分词: tricked 现在分词: tricking 第三人称单数: tricks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('script', '[skrɪpt]', 'n.剧本；脚本；手稿；手迹；字体；考卷', '1. The script won\'t play well. 那个剧本不适于在舞台上演出。 2. If the trust is verified, the script runs. 如果确定可信,则会运行该脚本。 3. The truthfulness of the script is undoubtable. 手稿的真实性是毋庸置疑的。 4. Sanskrit historically has had no single script associated with it. 梵语，从历史上看，没有单一的手稿与它联合起来。', '过去式: scripted 过去分词: scripted 现在分词: scripting 第三人称单数: scripts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fierce', '[fɪrs]', 'adj.强烈的；凶猛的；酷烈的', '1. What he said met with fierce opposition. 他的话语遭到激烈反对。 2. Because there is so much unemployment, the competition for jobs is fierce. 因为失业严重，求职的竞争十分激烈。 3. The postman was bitten by a fierce dog. 那个邮递员被一只恶狗咬了。 4. He has a very fierce look on his face. 他脸上一副凶相。', '副词: fiercely 比较级: fiercer 最高级: fiercest 名词: fierceness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('emigrate', '[\'emɪɡreɪt]', 'v.移居；移民', '1. I\'ll emigrate to the western woods. 我要移居到西部的丛林里去。 2. He\'s decided to emigrate and start a new life in America. 他决定移居美国，开始新的生活。 3. Many people had to emigrate during the Nazi period. 在纳粹党期间许多人不得不移民。 4. I don\'t like your plan to emigrate to Canada. 我不赞成你移民加拿大的计划。', '名词: emigration 过去式: emigrated 过去分词: emigrated 现在分词: emigrating 第三人称单数: emigrates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kitchen', '[\'kɪtʃɪn]', 'n.厨房；灶间；(全套)炊具', '1. I have to mop the kitchen floor at least once a day. 我每天至少要把厨房地板擦洗一次。 2. I guess there are mice in the kitchen. 我猜想厨房里有老鼠。 3. I was cooking in the kitchen when the telephone rang. 电话铃响的时候我正在厨房里做饭。 4. Everything in the kitchen is in good order. 厨房里的每样东西都井然有序。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nine', '[naɪn]', 'num.九', '1. I\'ll leave for Shanghai at nine. 九点钟，我将赴上海。 2. I have nine dolls in the bedroom. 我的卧室里有九个布娃娃。 3. Nine people came in and the remainder stayed outside. 9个人进来，余下的人留在外面。 4. Are you sure you can come by at nine? 你肯定你九点能来吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('apartment', '[ə\'pɑːrtmənt]', 'n.一套公寓房间', '1. I have an apartment in downtown Manhattan. 我在曼哈顿中心区有一套住房。 2. We are fascinated by the delicate interior design of the apartment. 我们被这所公寓的精致的室内装潢设计吸引。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pupil', '[\'pjuːpl]', 'n.小学生；弟子；【解】瞳孔', '1. The headmaster has made a decision of suspension of a pupil from school. 校长已经做出对一名学生停学处分的决定。 2. A teacher can\'t give individual attention to each pupil if his class is large. 如果班上的人数多，老师就不能给予个别辅导了。 3. The painting is the work of a pupil of Rembrandt. 这幅画是伦勃朗的一位弟子的作品。 4. The tenor was a pupil of Caruso. 这位男高音歌手师承卡鲁索。', '形容词: pupilar');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('till', '[tɪl]', 'prep.直到 ... 为止 conj.直到 ... 为止 n.放钱的抽屉；备用现金；[地质]冰碛土(物) v.耕作', '1. The meeting adjourned till five o\'clock. 会议延至五点召开。 2. Never put off till tomorrow what you can do today. 今日事今日毕。 3. Not till then did I realize the danger of the situation. 直到那个时候我才感到形势的危险。 4. Gee, I can hardly wait till it\'s dark. 哎呀，我简直等不到天黑了。', '形容词: tillable 过去式: tilled 过去分词: tilled 现在分词: tilling 第三人称单数: tills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cow', '[kaʊ]', 'n.母牛；雌象；雌鲸；雌犀牛；<俚><贬>女人 v.恐吓', '1. The cow has produced a calf. 这母牛生了一头小牛。 2. Do you know how to milk a cow? 你知道怎么挤牛奶吗？ 3. I\'m sure it was deliberately done to cow us. 我确信,这一事件经过精心策划,目的是恐吓我们。', '形容词: cowy 副词: cowedly 过去式: cowed 过去分词: cowed 现在分词: cowing 第三人称单数: cows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inherit', '[ɪn\'herɪt]', 'v.继承；遗传', '1. The eldest son will inherit the title. 长子将继承爵位。 2. She inherited a house from her father. 她从她父亲那儿继承了一所房子。 3. The two children both inherit left-handedness from their parents. 这两个孩子都从父母身上遗传了左撇子。', '名词: inheritor 过去式: inherited 过去分词: inherited 现在分词: inheriting 第三人称单数: inherits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('excuse', '[ɪk\'skjuːs]', 'vt.原谅；辩解 n.理由；辩解；借口', '1. Excuse me, but I must say you are completely wrong. 对不起，但是我必须说你完全错了。 2. I hope you will excuse me if I have to leave early. 如果我必须早些离开,希望你能原谅我。 3. He told a real whopper to excuse his lateness. 他撒了个大谎为自己的迟到辩解。 4. His excuse for being late was that he had missed the train. 他迟到的理由是没有赶上火车。', '形容词: excusable 副词: excusably 名词: excusableness 过去式: excused 过去分词: excused 现在分词: excusing 第三人称单数: excuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glory', '[\'ɡlɔːri]', 'n.光荣；荣誉；赞颂；壮丽 vi.自豪', '1. No road of flowers lead to glory. 没有一条通往光荣的道路是铺满鲜花的。 2. His brave deeds in the battle earned him everlasting glory. 他在那场战斗中的英勇事迹为他赢得了永恒的荣誉。 3. They are driven by a craving for personal glory. 对个人荣誉的渴望驱动着他们。 4. The minister was bathed in glory when she arranged a peaceful settlement. 这位女部长达成了一项和平协定后，沉浸在一片赞颂声中。 5. He gloried in his winning the championship. 他因获得冠军而洋洋得意。', '名词复数: glories 过去式: gloried 过去分词: gloried 现在分词: glorying 第三人称单数: glories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acquaint', '[ə\'kweɪnt]', 'vt.使了解；使熟知；告知', '1. We should first try to acquaint ourselves with the facts. 我们先要想法了解事实。 2. These books acquaint Chinese readers with the ancient cultures of these lands. 这些书帮助中国读者了解这些地区的古代文化。 3. You must acquaint yourself with your new duties. 你必须熟悉自己的新职务。 4. Please acquaint him with my arrival. 请通知他我到了。', '过去式: acquainted 过去分词: acquainted 现在分词: acquainting 第三人称单数: acquaints');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spiral', '[\'spaɪrəl]', 'n.螺旋；螺旋形之物；不断恶化、增加或减少 v.螺旋移动；盘旋上升；不断恶化、增加或减少 adj.螺旋形的；盘旋的', '1. Society invariably moves forward in a spiral. 社会的运动总是采取螺旋形前进的。 2. This caused a downward spiral into depression. 这使经济下滑恶化为经济萧条。 3. The smoke spiraled upwards. 那股烟袅袅上升。 4. Prices are still spiralling. 价格仍然在急剧上涨。 5. A snails shell is spiral in form. 蜗牛的外壳形状是螺旋形的。', '副词: spirally 名词: spirality 过去式: spiraled/spiralled 过去分词: spiraled/spiralled 现在分词: spiraling/spiralling 第三人称单数: spirals/spirals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stand', '[stænd]', 'v.站立；忍受；位于；停滞 n.站立；货摊；停顿；看台', '1. I don\'t think the chair is firm enough to stand on. 我觉得这椅子不够稳固,不能站人。 2. I twisted my ankle, and I couldn\'t stand up. 我的脚踝扭伤,简直无法站起来。 3. She is funny, but I can\'t stand her. 她滑稽,但我无法忍受她。 4. Several pine trees stand erect on the hillside. 几棵青松挺立在山坡上。 5. He took his stand near the window. 他站在窗旁。', '名词: stander 过去式: stood 过去分词: stood 现在分词: standing 第三人称单数: stands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ensure', '[ɪn\'ʃʊr]', 'vt.担保；保证；使安全；确保', '1. We have worked closely with the Deaf community first, on passage of ADA, and most recently, to ensure that the Act is enforced. 我们最近经常在ada路边的聋人社会附近工作，可以担保该法案得到了实施。 2. I can\'t ensure that he will be there on time. 我不能担保他会及时到那儿。 3. This medicine will ensure you a good night\'s sleep. 这药保证能让你好好睡一觉。 4. People should wash regularly to ensure personal hygiene. 人们应经常洗澡以保证个人卫生。', '过去式: ensured 过去分词: ensured 现在分词: ensuring 第三人称单数: ensures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tremble', '[\'trembl]', 'n.战悚；颤抖 v.发抖；忧虑；震颤', '1. His remarks struck a tremble into her heart. 他的话令她感到不寒而栗。 2. There was a tremble in her voice. 她声音颤抖。 3. The dog was all of a tremble with cold. 这条狗冻得全身发抖。 4. He was trembling with rage. 他气得发抖。', '形容词: trembly 副词: tremblingly 名词: trembler 过去式: trembled 过去分词: trembled 现在分词: trembling 第三人称单数: trembles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suppose', '[sə\'poʊz]', 'vt.假设；假定；认为；想；应该；让(虚拟语气) vi.推测', '1. Suppose you have a thousand dollars, what will you do with it. 假设你有一千美元，你会用它做什么。 2. Let us suppose another planet with conditions similar to those on the earth. 让我们假定另外有一个具有和地球上相似条件的行星。 3. Some religions suppose that there is a Heaven physically above the earth. 一些宗教认为地球上面真有一个天国。 4. I suppose we shall be having some sort of celebration for the bride. 我想我们还是来为新娘庆贺一番吧。 5. I suppose he would be about fifty when he obtained a doctorate. 我推测他获得博士学位时大概是五十岁左右。', '过去式: supposed 过去分词: supposed 现在分词: supposing 第三人称单数: supposes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guess', '[ɡes]', 'v.推测；猜中；以为 n.猜测；猜想', '1. I don\'t really know, I\'m just guessing. 我真的不知道, 我仅仅是猜想。 2. We could only guess at her motives. 我们只能猜测她的动机 3. She guessed the right answer at once. 她立刻猜出了正确的答案。 4. He guessed the number of the beans in the jar. 他猜出了缸里豆子有多少。 5. I\'ll give you three guesses. 我让你猜三次。', '名词: guesser 过去式: guessed 过去分词: guessed 现在分词: guessing 第三人称单数: guesses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('editor', '[\'edɪtər]', 'n.编辑；编者；影片剪辑装置', '1. The editor hacked the story to bits. 编辑把那篇小说改得面目全非。 2. The editor struck out the whole paragraph. 编辑把整段全删掉了。 3. He is an associate editor of the newspaper. 他是报纸的副主编。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plan', '[plæn]', 'n.计划；方法；策略；设计图；平面图 v.打算；安排；计划；设计', '1. As far as I am concerned, I\'m not against your plan. 就我而言，我并不反对你的计划。 2. Then a courageous police officer came up with a daring, desperate plan. 然后,一位勇敢的警官孤注一掷想出了一个大胆的方法。 3. The police worked out a plan to catch the thief. 警察制定出了策略捉贼。 4. Jack traced out the plan of a house quickly. 杰克很快描画出一座房屋的平面图。 5. Where do you plan to spend your holiday? 你打算去哪里度假？', '名词: planner 过去式: planned 过去分词: planned 现在分词: planning 第三人称单数: plans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('possibility', '[ˌpɑːsə\'bɪləti]', 'n.可能；可能性；可能的事情；潜在的价值', '1. I see great possibilities in the scheme. 我看这计划很可能成功。 2. We must accept the possibility that we might be wrong. 我们必须承认，我们有可能搞错了。 3. She saw the possibilities of the scheme from the beginning. 她从一开始就预见到这计划可能成功。 4. We can\'t exclude the possibility that it will rain. 我们不能排除天会下雨的可能性。', '名词复数: possibilities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('member', '[\'membər]', 'n.成员；会员；部分', '1. He declared himself a member of their party. 他声明他本人是他们政党的成员。 2. I am a member of our school football club. 我是我们学校足球俱乐部的成员。 3. The club took in a new member last week. 俱乐部上星期又吸收了一名新会员。 4. He was a founder member of the club. 他是俱乐部的创始会员之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('load', '[loʊd]', 'n.负荷；重担；装载量 v.装载；给(枪)装子弹；[计算机] 装入', '1. A plane can carry only so much load after all. 一架飞机终归只能承载那么多的负荷。 2. The load is too heavy and the supports buckle . 负荷过重，支柱坍下来。 3. She will not shove the heavy load onto others. 她不愿意把重担推给别人。 4. The baker contracted for a load of flour. 面包师订了买一车面粉的合同。 5. We must use mechanical hoisting to load the goods. 我们必须用起重机来装载货物。', '过去式: loaded 过去分词: loaded 现在分词: loading 第三人称单数: loads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('indication', '[ˌɪndɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.指示；表示；迹象', '1. Did they give you any indication? 他们给你指示了吗? 2. Did he give you any indication of his feelings? 他向你表示过他的感情吗？ 3. There are some indications that the prices will rise. 有迹象表明物价将上涨。 4. There is every indication that the price will rise. 各种迹象表明价格将上涨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resistant', '[rɪ\'zɪstənt]', 'adj.抵抗的；反抗的', '1. A healthy diet creates a body resistant to disease. 保健饮食有助于增强体内对疾病的抵抗力。 2. The high walls of rock are made of weather-resistant quartzite. 那高高的岩石墙壁是由对风化有抵抗的石英岩组成的。 3. This new type of infection is resistant to antibiotics. 这种新的传染病对抗菌素有抗药性。 4. They imposed their government by force on the resistant population. 他们以武力把自己的统治强加在持反抗态度的人民头上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('telephone', '[\'telɪfoʊn]', 'n.电话 v.打电话', '1. Let me note down your address and telephone number. 让我记下你的地址和电话号码。 2. He put the telephone bill down as a business cost. 他把电话费用作为办公费记下。 3. You can telephone your order through to the shop. 你可以打电话向商店购货。 4. Telephone me when you get through. 你的工作完成以后打电话告诉我。', '名词: telephoner 过去式: telephoned 过去分词: telephoned 现在分词: telephoning 第三人称单数: telephones');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('romance', '[\'roʊmæns]', 'n.浪漫史；爱情故事；冒险故事；传奇文学；虚构 vt.<口>向…求爱 vi.讲虚构故事', '1. They kept the romance alive in their marriage for 35 years. 他们35年的婚姻生活一直保持着浪漫色彩 2. That romance movie is a real tear-jerker. 那部言情电影真是令人泪下如注。 3. His romance and adventure were battering at the conventions. 他的传奇和冒险故事粉碎着传统。 4. The biography relishes too much of romance. 这篇传记中传奇色彩太浓。 5. She would often romance about her bitter experiences. 她总是夸大其词地讲她的痛苦经历。', '名词: romancer 过去式: romanced 过去分词: romanced 现在分词: romancing 第三人称单数: romances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('former', '[\'fɔːrmər]', 'adj.前者的；前任的；以前的 n.创造者；<英>学校某一年级的学生', '1. Of these two men, the former is dead but the latter is still alive. 这两个人中，前者已死，而后者仍然活着。 2. Mr. Heath is the former Prime Minister of Britain. 希思先生是英国前任首相。 3. I paid a visit to my former English teacher. 我拜访了我以前的英语老师。 4. Many of his former supporters voted against him. 他以前的许多支持者投票反对他。 5. a former of ideas 想出主意者', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wisdom', '[\'wɪzdəm]', 'n.智慧；明智；才智；聪明；至理名言', '1. She had acquired much wisdom during her long life. 她经年累月造就了很高的智慧。 2. He attributes his wisdom to his teachers. 他认为他的智慧来自于老师。 3. We grow in wisdom as we grow older. 我们随着年龄增长而更加明智。 4. A flow of words is no proof of wisdom. 口若悬河，不能证明真有才智。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('operation', '[ˌɑːpə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.操作；运转；经营；行动；手术；运算；生效；（复）运筹学', '1. The operation of this machine is simple. 这个机器的操作很简单。 2. I am skillful with computer operation. 我的计算机操作技术很好。 3. We hope we will finalise the operation before the transfer window closes. 我们希望在转会窗口关闭之前完成运转。 4. He calls himself the managing director but his company is just a Mickey Mouse operation that he runs from his own house. 他自称为总经理,但他的公司就是再他自己家里经营的一个微不足道的商号。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('time', '[taɪm]', 'n.时间；时代；时期；倍；次数；节拍 v.为…安排时间；计时；[体]在某一时刻击球 adj.时间的；定时的；分期（付款）的；定期的', '1. Only time will tell if you are right. 只有时间才能证明你是否正确。 2. Reading occupies most of my free time. 阅读占去了我大部分的闲暇时间。 3. I referred to my watch for the exact time. 我看了一下手表好知道准确的时间。 4. Closing time at this pub is eleven o\' clock. 这酒馆的打烊时间是十一点。 5. The experienced car racer can always time his start to perfection. 那位经验丰富的车手总是能够完美地掌握出发的时间。 6. The earth is divided into 24 time zones. 地球被分为二十四个时区。', '过去式: timed 过去分词: timed 现在分词: timing 第三人称单数: times');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lump', '[lʌmp]', 'n.块；团；笨重的人；瘤 v.使成块；形成团状；归并；(笨重地)移动', '1. The surgeon excised the lump from her breast. 外科医生切除了她乳房的肿块。 2. It was amazing to watch the lump of clay take life beneath the sculptor\'s hands. 看着泥团在雕塑家手下成了栩栩如生的形象真令人惊叹。 3. The heat brought his fingers back to life,but did nothing for the cold lump in the pit of his stomach. 炉火使手指缓过劲来了，但对他肚子里的那团凉气却无济于事。 4. Since the urease activity in soil is close correlated with the growth of stem lump mustard and soil metabolism, which is a key indicator of soil ecology and soil fertility. 土壤脲酶活性高低反映出茎瘤芥生长和土壤代谢状况，可作为茎瘤芥土壤生态和肥力水平的一个良好指标。 5. The oatmeal lumps if you don\'t stir it well. 如果你不好好搅拌，麦片粥会结块。', '过去式: lumped 过去分词: lumped 现在分词: lumping 第三人称单数: lumps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exact', '[ɪɡ\'zækt]', 'adj.精密严谨的；确切的', '1. She\'s a very exact person. 她是个一丝不苟的人。 2. We need exact instruments. 我们需要精密仪器。 3. What is the exact size of the room? 这个房间的确切面积是多少？ 4. It was difficult to tell her exact age. 很难说出她的确切年龄。', '形容词: exactable 名词: exactness 过去式: exacted 过去分词: exacted 现在分词: exacting 第三人称单数: exacts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('limp', '[lɪmp]', 'n.跛行 adj.柔软的；无力的；软弱的 vi.跛行；蹒跚', '1. Two weeks later, the dog could walk with a limp. 两周后，狗儿可以跛行了。 2. The injury left him with a permanent limp. 他受伤后就一直瘸了。 3. This young man is wearing a limp grey sweater. 这个年轻人穿着一件柔软的灰色运动衫。 4. The man\'s shrieked whistle struck his limp ears. 男人尖细的口哨声传到它那柔软的耳朵里。 5. He that lives with cripples learns to limp. 近朱者赤，近墨者黑。', '副词: limply 比较级: limper 最高级: limpest 名词: limpness 过去式: limped 过去分词: limped 现在分词: limping 第三人称单数: limps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('number', '[\'nʌmbə(r)]', 'n.号码；数量；数字 v.总计；编号；编号；把 ... 算作', '1. He picked a winning number on the first draw. 他第一次便抽到一个中奖号码。 2. I slipped up and gave you the wrong phone number. 我粗心大意给错了你电话号码。 3. The number of fish in coastal waters has decreased. 沿海鱼的数量已减少了。 4. The number of your finger is ten. 你双手手指的总数是10。 5. The students of our department numbered in the hundreds. 我们系的学生总共有几百人。', '名词: numberer 过去式: numbered 过去分词: numbered 现在分词: numbering 第三人称单数: numbers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beer', '[bɪr]', 'n.啤酒', '1. He bought a barrel of beer. 他买了一桶啤酒。 2. I like drinking beer. 我喜欢喝啤酒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pessimistic', '[ˌpesɪ\'mɪstɪk]', 'adj.悲观的；悲观主义的', '1. I have to say I\'m rather pessimistic. 我得说我相当悲观。 2. Her pessimistic attitude turns him off. 她那悲观的态度很令他不高兴。 3. There is a pessimistic tone to what he is saying. 他的话语中带着悲观的调子。 4. This might account for his pessimistic views. 这也许是他持悲观主义观点的原因。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('amaze', '[ə\'meɪz]', 'vt.使吃惊；使惊异 vi.惊讶 n.吃惊；好奇', '1. He amazed me by his audacity. 他的无理让我惊骇。 2. I was amazed to find her there. 发现她在那，我感到很吃惊。 3. We were amazed at the change in his appearance. 他的样子变得使我们大为惊讶。 4. Modern technology never ceases to amaze me. 现代科技总是令我惊讶不已。 5. He stood in amaze at the sight . 他看到那种景象,惊愕得呆呆地站在那里。', '副词: amazedly 名词: amazedness 过去式: amazed 过去分词: amazed 现在分词: amazing 第三人称单数: amazes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('odds', '[ɑːdz]', 'n.机率；可能性；差别；投注赔率；让步；优势', '1. The odds are against us. 我们成功的机会很小。 2. His odds are very poor after he sprained his wrist. 他扭伤了手腕，获胜的可能性极小。 3. It makes no odds whether Henry goes or stays. 亨利去也好留也好都没有什么关系。 4. The horse was running at odds of ten to one. 那匹马参赛赔率是十比一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cheat', '[tʃiːt]', 'vt.欺骗；骗取 vi.作弊；行骗 n.骗子；欺骗', '1. We were on our honor not to cheat the customers. 我们以名誉担保不欺骗顾客。 2. It is contemptible to cheat friends. 欺骗朋友是卑劣的。 3. They cheat the old woman of her house and money. 他们骗取了老妇人的房屋和钱财。 4. I would rather fail than cheat in the examination. 我宁愿考不及格，也不愿意考试作弊。 5. He is a shameless cheat. 他是个无耻的骗子。', '副词: cheatingly 名词: cheater 过去式: cheated 过去分词: cheated 现在分词: cheating 第三人称单数: cheats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('risk', '[rɪsk]', 'n.危险；风险；投资报酬的风险 vt.冒 ... 的危险；承受...的风险', '1. He saved my life at the risk of his own. 他冒着自己的生命危险救了我的命。 2. Investors in Central Asia have to face political risk. 在中亚,投资者还得面临政治风险。 3. Loans to farmers are now considered to be a bad risk. 贷款给农民现在被认为要承受糟糕的投资报酬风险。 4. If you don\'t warm up before taking exercise, you risk injuring yourself. 假如运动前不做准备活动,你就有受伤的危险。', '名词: risker 过去式: risked 过去分词: risked 现在分词: risking 第三人称单数: risks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('geometry', '[dʒi\'ɑːmətri]', 'n.几何；几何学', '1. I feel that geometry is a difficult subject. 我认为几何是一门难学的课程。 2. Today we have a lesson in geometry. 今天，我们有一节几何课。 3. Leon didn\'t finish his geometry homework because his mind kept jumping the track to think about the new girl in class. 利昂没完成几何作业，因为他思想总在开小差，想着班上新来的女生。 4. The boy puzzled his way through geometry. 那男孩煞费苦心地钻研几何学。', '名词: geometrician 名词复数: geometries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('department', '[dɪ\'pɑːrtmənt]', 'n.部门；系；科；处；局 n.知识范围', '1. He worked in community welfare department. 他在社会福利部工作。 2. He works in the drapery department of the store. 他在商店的纺织品部工作。 3. He was elected the dean of our department. 他被选为我们系的系主任。 4. The students of our department numbered in the hundreds. 我们系的学生总共有几百人。 5. Don\'t ask me about our finances: that\'s my wife\'s department. 我们家的经济情况你别问我,那是我妻子的事。', '形容词: departmental 副词: departmentally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('excel', '[ɪk\'sel]', 'vt.优于；超过 vi.胜出 n.[计] 电子表格（软件名称）', '1. He excels in painting. 他擅长绘画。 2. His wife excels him in strategical ability. 他的妻子在战略上胜过他。 3. We strive to excel in bringing out our clients vision and style. 我们努力在带给我们的客户不同的观念和风格上优于他人。 4. They each excel in their respective fields. 他们在各自领域里都是出类拔萃的。 5. He always hopes that his son will excel over him someday. 他总是希望他的儿子有天能胜过他. 6. Excel is widely applied in the vacuum metrology. 在真空计量领域中，Excel电子表格软件得到了广泛的应用。', '过去式: excelled 过去分词: excelled 现在分词: excelling 第三人称单数: excels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('population', '[ˌpɑːpju\'leɪʃn]', 'n.人口；(全体)居民；群体', '1. What is the population of this country? 这个国家的人口是多少？ 2. The density of population in this city is very high. 这个城市的人口密度非常高。 3. There has been a steady decrease in population in this city. 这个城市的人口在持续下降。 4. We have a growing population and therefore we need more food. 我们的人口在增长，因此我们需要更多的食物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('neck', '[nek]', 'n.颈；脖子 v.搂着脖子亲吻；（使）变窄', '1. The giraffe is characterized by its very long neck. 长颈鹿以其长颈为特徵. 2. The neck of my guitar is broken. 我吉他的琴颈坏了。 3. The doctor operated the patient on the neck. 医生给病人的颈部动手术。 4. She wears a gold chain around her neck. 她脖子上戴着一条金项链。 5. The two of them were necking on a park bench. 他们俩在公园的长凳上拥抱亲吻。', '形容词: neckless 过去式: necked 过去分词: necked 现在分词: necking 第三人称单数: necks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accurate', '[\'ækjərət]', 'adj.准确的；精确的', '1. Hearsay definitely can\'t be regarded as accurate information. 道听途说的决然不能算作很准确的消息。 2. The manager impressed on his office staff the importance of keeping accurate records. 经理让办公室职员认识到做精确记录的重要性。', '副词: accurately 名词: accurateness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fabulous', '[\'fæbjələs]', 'adj.极好的；巨大的；传说中的', '1. I must go to taste your fabulous cooking. 我一定去尝一尝您精湛的烹调。 2. The minutes of evening twilight are fabulous . 短暂的黄昏景色真令人惊叹。 3. You look fabulous, you\'ll knock them dead tonight. 你看上去漂亮极了,今晚肯定把他们迷倒。 4. The museum has a fabulous collection of jewels. 该博物馆有著惊人的珠宝收藏。', '副词: fabulously 名词: fabulousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cunning', '[\'kʌnɪŋ]', 'adj.狡猾的；有眼光的；精巧的；可爱的 n.【C】狡诈；灵巧', '1. Many politicians are cunning sophists. 许多政客都是狡猾的诡辩家。 2. The fox is known for its cleverness and cunning. 狐狸的机敏和狡猾是人所共知的。 3. She showed her cunning in the way she avoided answering the question. 她对问题避而不答，显示出她很狡猾。 4. He devised a very cunning scheme to help her. 他想出一个帮助她的很好的办法。 5. The fox is believed to have a great deal of cunning. 人们相信狐狸十分狡猾。', '副词: cunningly 名词: cunningness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slipper', '[\'slɪpər]', 'n.拖鞋', '1. No slipper is allowed in the laboratory. 实验室里不允许穿拖鞋。 2. His father meted out punishment with a slipper. 他的老爸用拖鞋来给他颜色看。', '形容词: slippered');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('petition', '[pə\'tɪʃn]', 'n.请愿书；祈求；申请 vi.请愿；祈求 vt.向 ... 请愿，请求', '1. Many subscribers\' names are in the petition. 请愿书上有很多签名者的名字。 2. They signed a petition in support of the workers\' demands. 他们在请愿书上签名，支持工人的请求。 3. She made a silent petition to God for help. 她默默地祈求上帝给予帮助。 4. She filed a petition for divorce. 她提出了离婚申请。 5. I can petition for Junie\'s custody. 我可以申请做琼妮的监护人。 6. She petitioned her neighbor to turn down the radio. 她请求邻居把收音机关小点声。', '形容词: petitionary 名词: petitioner 过去式: petitioned 过去分词: petitioned 现在分词: petitioning 第三人称单数: petitions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('despise', '[dɪ\'spaɪz]', 'vt.轻视', '1. He claims to despise riches. 他宣称蔑视钱财。 2. You must not despise a man because he is poor. 你不可因一个人贫穷而轻视他。 3. I despise his refusing to accept responsibility. 他拒不承担责任，我鄙视他。 4. It is incorrect to despise woman. 轻视妇女是错误的。', '名词: despisal 过去式: despised 过去分词: despised 现在分词: despising 第三人称单数: despises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tolerant', '[\'tɑːlərənt]', 'adj.宽容的；容忍的', '1. Of all the girls, she is the most tolerant. 在所有的姑娘当中，她是最宽容的。 2. As a man, you should be tolerant and magnanimous. 一个男人家，应该宽容大度些！ 3. A priest must learn to be tolerant and always suffer fools gladly. 一个神父必须学会宽容和永远甘心容忍愚妄的人。 4. He is not very tolerant of criticism. 他不大能容忍批评。', '副词: tolerantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('there', '[ðer]', 'adv.在那里；到那里；从那里 pron.表示存在（与be连用） n.那个地方；那一点', '1. He has a house there and a cottage near the sea. 他在那里有一所房子,在海边还有一个小屋。 2. He drove quickly in order to get there on time. 他开得飞快,以便准时赶到那里。 3. Don\'t panic! We\'ll soon get you out of there. 别害怕,我们马上就把你从那里带出去。 4. He, with his mother, lives near there. 他和他的母亲住在附近的那个地方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('necessary', '[\'nesəseri]', 'adj.必要的；必然的 n.必需品', '1. She will make necessary arrangements. 她会作好必要的准备。 2. If necessary, please warehouse the goods. 如有必要，请将该货存入仓库。 3. The necessary outcome of a war is a fall in production. 战争带来的必然结果就是生产力下降。', '名词复数: necessaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('textile', '[\'tekstaɪl]', 'n.纺织品', '1. He intends to retail textile goods. 他打算零售纺织品。 2. This textile feels like real leather. 这种纺织品摸上去象真皮似的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tend', '[tend]', 'v.趋向；易于；朝向 v.照料；照管', '1. Weeds tend to displace other plants. 杂草越来越多，有取代其他植物之势。 2. During the interview, some interviewees tend to exaggerate. 面试时,有些面试者会有夸大的倾向。 3. He\'s a good salesman, but his offhand manner does tend to put people off. 他是个很好的推销员，可是他那随便的态度容易使人产生反感。 4. Prices are tending upward. 物价在上涨。 5. Mother being ill, he had to tend her at home. 母亲病了,他得在家照料她。', '过去式: tended 过去分词: tended 现在分词: tending 第三人称单数: tends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stuff', '[stʌf]', 'n.东西；原料；材料 n.素质；本质；废物；无用的想法；废话，蠢话 vt.塞满；填满', '1. Get rid of that stuff in the garage. 把车库里那些没有用的东西处理掉。 2. I\'ve got quite a lot of stuff to read. 我有许多东西要读。 3. We must as well buy our own stuff. 我们不妨自己去买原料。 4. Some parts nowadays are made of plastic or similar stuff. 现在有些零件是由塑料或类似的材料制造的。 5. The young man has good stuff in him. 那个年轻人素质很好。 6. He stuffed the suitcase with his clothes. 他把衣服塞满手提箱。', '名词: stuffer 过去式: stuffed 过去分词: stuffed 现在分词: stuffing 第三人称单数: stuffs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prefer', '[prɪ\'fɜːr]', 'vt.宁可；较喜欢；提出（控告）', '1. I would prefer to stay home rather than go out on such a rainy day. 在这种雨天，我宁可待在家也不出门。 2. All this gracious living is not for me；I prefer the simple life. 这种优裕的生活对我不合适；我还是更喜欢简朴的生活。 3. Which one do you prefer, an apple or an orange? 你想要哪个，苹果还是橘子？ 4. Police preferred charges against him for theft. 警方指控他有偷窃行为。', '名词: preferrer 过去式: preferred 过去分词: preferred 现在分词: preferring 第三人称单数: prefers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('different', '[\'dɪfrənt]', 'adj.不同的；差异的；分别的；各不相同的', '1. The two doctors made different diagnosis of my disease. 两位医生对我的病作出了不同的诊断。 2. He\'s a different man from what he was 10 years ago. 他和十年前不一样。 3. You can\'t imagine how different it is from the John Grier Home. 你很难想象这里与约翰·格利尔孤儿院有多大的区别。 4. I called on three different occasions, but he was out. 我打了三次电话', '副词: differently 名词: difference');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tailor', '[\'teɪlər]', 'n.裁缝 vt.缝制；调整使适合 vi.做裁缝', '1. This tailor is famous for making good suit. 这位裁缝以做高级西装而出名。 2. The tailor made a suit for Dick. 这位裁缝师为迪克做了一套西装。 3. He tailored me a tweed suit. 他为我缝制了一套苏格兰粗呢的衣服。 4. He wears a beautifully tailored suit. 他穿了一套定做的漂亮西装。 5. He established himeself as a tailor. 他以做裁缝为业。', '过去式: tailored 过去分词: tailored 现在分词: tailoring 第三人称单数: tailors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impulse', '[\'ɪmpʌls]', 'n.冲动；心血来潮；神经冲动；[物]冲量；[电]脉冲 vt.推动', '1. He bought the house on an impulse. 他凭一时冲动买下了这所房子。 2. We were seized by a sudden impulse to run. 我们身不由己突然想跑。 3. On impulse, I picked up the phone and rang my sister in Australia. 我一时心血来潮，拿起话筒就给在澳大利亚的妹妹打了个电话。 4. He had a sudden impulse to stand up and sing. 他突然心血来潮，想站起来歌唱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suspect', '[sə\'spekt]', 'v.怀疑；猜想 n.嫌疑犯 adj.可疑的；不可信的', '1. They suspected an ambush. 他们怀疑有埋伏。 2. I suspect he was lying by the boy\'s abnormal behaviour. 从那个男孩的反常举动中,我怀疑他在撒谎。 3. Just at that time, I began to suspect whether to tell her that matter. 只是在那个时候,我开始怀疑我是否应该告诉她那件事。 4. She has more intelligence than we suspected her to possess. 她的智慧比我们猜想的要高。 5. He\'s a prime suspect in the murder case. 他是这次谋杀案的主要怀疑对象 6. His motives are highly suspect. 他的动机是高度令人生疑的。', '过去式: suspected 过去分词: suspected 现在分词: suspecting 第三人称单数: suspects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consensus', '[kən\'sensəs]', 'n.一致；同意；共识', '1. The two parties have reached a consensus. 这两个政党达成了一致意见。 2. It would be a good idea to predict which proposal is most likely to achieve consensus. 不妨研究一下哪项提案最有可能获得一致同意。 3. Yet the events of the past two years have called that consensus in question. 然而,过去两年来发生的各种事件使人们对这一共识产生了疑虑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soup', '[suːp]', 'n.汤；羹 v.增大威力', '1. I made some gravy soup for my husband. 我给我丈夫做了一些肉汤。 2. He had spoiled the soup by putting in too much salt. 他往汤里放盐太多，把汤给糟蹋了。 3. This soup is a spicy variation on a traditional favourite. 这种汤是在一种受欢迎的传统汤羹中加了香料。 4. We use top quality fresh raw materials for the meat soup and squid soup which taste specially delicious. 我们采用上等材料制成风味特佳的各种羹类食品，鲜味可口。 5. The engineer tried to soup up the engine. 工程师试图加大这台发动机的马力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('paperback', '[\'peɪpərbæk]', 'n.纸封面本；普及本；平装书', '1. This writer\'s books are all issued as paperback. 这位作家的书都是平装书。 2. We are doing a special promotion of our paperback list. 我们正在搞推销平装书的特别宣传活动。', '形容词: paperbacked');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dimension', '[ˌdɪ\'menʃən]', 'n. 尺寸； 次元； 容积； 维度； 范围； 方面 vt. 标尺寸； 形成 ... 尺寸', '1. Height is an external dimension. 高是外部尺寸。 2. When a dimension\'s origin is in doubt use the datums specified. 当不能确定尺寸原点时，使用规定的基准。 3. The fifth dimension creates everything that is on earth. 第五次元创造了地球上所有的东西。 4. The crystal extractors from that dimension cross through all dimensions. 从那个次元的水晶提取器穿越所有的次元。 5. We were told to dimension off the plots. 吩咐我们在图表上标出尺寸。', '形容词: dimensional 副词: dimensionally 名词: dimensionality 过去式: dimensioned 过去分词: dimensioned 现在分词: dimensioning 第三人称单数: dimensions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feature', '[\'fiːtʃər]', 'n.特征；特色；容貌；特写；故事片 vt.以 ... 为特色 vi.起重要作用', '1. Their candor is a very pleasing feature. 他们的坦白是很愉快的特征。 2. Wet weather is a feature of life in this area. 天气潮湿是这个地区生活的一个特色。 3. Her mouth is her best feature. 她的嘴是她容貌上最好看的部分。 4. The local newspaper ran a feature on child labor. 地方报纸登载一篇有关童工的特写。 5. This restaurant seems to feature vegetarian dishes. 这家餐厅似乎以素菜为其特色。 6. Jazz and Blues feature prominently in the magazine. 爵士和蓝调在杂志中占重要篇幅。', '过去式: featured 过去分词: featured 现在分词: featuring 第三人称单数: features');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wink', '[wɪŋk]', 'n.眨眼；使眼色；瞬间 v.眨眼；使眼色；闪烁', '1. She did not understand the significance of my wink. 她没有领会我眨眼的意思。 2. He tipped me the wink not to buy at that price. 他眨眼暗示我按那个价格就不要买。 3. I\'ll tip you the wink when it\'s safe to come in. 可以安全进来时，我会向你使眼色的。 4. Then in the wink of an eye, the eight old men all turn into five- or six-year-old children. 说着,八位老者一眨眼工夫,忽然全变成五六岁的儿童了。 5. She winked at me. 她向我眨眼。', '过去式: winked 过去分词: winked 现在分词: winking 第三人称单数: winks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('proposal', '[prə\'poʊzl]', 'n.求婚；建议；提议', '1. She had had many proposals but preferred to remain single. 许多人向她求过婚, 但她愿过独身生活。 2. The manager made a proposal for uniting the two companies. 经理提出了将两家公司联合起来的建议。 3. Various proposals were put forward by the employees for increasing sales. 员工们摆出了各种提高销售额的提议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('doom', '[duːm]', 'n.毁灭；厄运；判决；死亡 vt.注定；判定', '1. The dictator met his doom after ten years of rule. 独裁者统治了十年终於完蛋了。 2. The slightest miscalculations in trajectory can spell doom for a successful space mission . 对轨道的细小的计算错误可以意味着对成功的太空任务的灭顶之灾。 3. She had then offered him the chance to baffle his doom. 当时她向他提供战胜厄运的机会。 4. The doom which I have passed upon her is irrevocable 我对她下的判决是不能挽回的。 5. Everyone is doomed to die. 每个人都是注定要死的。', '过去式: doomed 过去分词: doomed 现在分词: dooming 第三人称单数: dooms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('genetic', '[dʒə\'netɪk]', 'adj.遗传的；基因的；起源的', '1. He chose genetic engineering to be his lifelong career. 他选择了遗传工程学作为终生的事业。 2. Most chromomeres contain a genetic unit. 绝大多数染色粒包含一个遗传单位。 3. The disease is caused by a genetic defect. 这种疾病的起因是基因缺陷。 4. Every living thing has its own genetic chips. 每种生物都有自己的基因芯片。', '副词: genetically 异体字: genetical');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('decide', '[dɪ\'saɪd]', 'v.决定；判断；断定', '1. That decided me to leave my job. 那件事使我决定离职。 2. A chance meeting decided my career. 偶然的会面决定了我的事业。 3. He decided to get married. 他决定结婚。 4. Don\'t decide on important matters too quickly. 不要过于匆忙地对重要的事情作决定。', '形容词: decidable 名词: decidability 过去式: decided 过去分词: decided 现在分词: deciding 第三人称单数: decides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('delay', '[dɪ\'leɪ]', 'v.耽搁；推迟；延误 n.耽搁；延期；推迟', '1. It was impossible to delay her at such a crisis. 在这样一个紧要关头来耽搁她是不可能的。 2. We decided to delay our wedding until next year. 我们决定把婚礼推迟到明年。 3. Our plane was delayed by fog. 我们的飞机因大雾而误点了。 4. The weather is responsible for the delay. 由于天气关系才耽搁了。', '名词: delayer 过去式: delayed 过去分词: delayed 现在分词: delaying 第三人称单数: delays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('speculate', '[\'spekjuleɪt]', 'vt.推测 vi.投机；深思', '1. The doctors speculate that he died of cancer. 医生推测他死于癌症。 2. Can you speculate how such damage might arise? 你能否想出这种伤害是怎样引起的? 3. He likes to speculate on the stock market. 他喜欢炒股。 4. It\'s dangerous to speculate. 做投机买卖是很危险的。', '过去式: speculated 过去分词: speculated 现在分词: speculating 第三人称单数: speculates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poll', '[poʊl]', 'n.民意测验；投票；票数 v.做民意测验；获得 ... 票', '1. We are going to conduct a public opinion poll. 我们将进行民意测验。 2. The president has a favourable rating in the opinion poll. 民意测验对总统评价很好。 3. They organized a poll to elect a president. 他们组织了一次投票选举总统。 4. The final result of the poll will be known tomorrow. 投票结果将于明天公布。 5. We can poll using a questionnaire. 我们可以用调查问卷进行民意测验。', '名词: poller 过去式: polled 过去分词: polled 现在分词: polling 第三人称单数: polls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transform', '[træns\'fɔːm]', 'vt.改变；转换 vi.改变；变形；变态', '1. She is responsible for the character part of the hero\'s devoted mother. 她负责这个主人公的忠诚的母亲的角色部分。 2. The magician transformed the frog into a princess. 魔术师把青蛙变成了公主。 3. His plans were transformed overnight into reality. 他的计划迅速变为现实。 4. We should try to transform heat into power. 我们应该设法将热转化为能量。', '形容词: transformable 过去式: transformed 过去分词: transformed 现在分词: transforming 第三人称单数: transforms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fuse', '[fjuːz]', 'n.保险丝；导火线；引线 vt.熔化；融合；装导线；装引信于 vi.熔化；融合', '1. The fuse-box is in the kitchen. 保险丝盒子在厨房里。 2. Changing a fuse is one of those fiddly jobs I hate. 我最不愿意干换保险丝这类活儿了。 3. It seems that you\'ve blown a fuse. 看样子你把保险丝烧断了。 4. I know how to mend a fuse and I don\'t need you shoving your oar in! 我知道怎麽弄保险丝，用不著你管！ 5. We fuse copper and tin to make bronze. 我们把铜和锡熔制成青铜。 6. The metal will fuse at a relatively low temperature. 这金属在不太高的温度下熔化。', '过去式: fused/fuzed 过去分词: fused/fuzed 现在分词: fusing/fuzing 第三人称单数: fuses/fuzes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('retort', '[rɪ\'tɔːrt]', 'v.反驳；回嘴；反击 n.反驳；顶嘴', '1. He retorted that it was my fault as much as his. 他反驳说我的错误并不比他的小。 2. The analysts could retort only that the geometric proofs were clumsy and inelegant. 分析学家只能回嘴说几何的证明是笨拙而不优美的。 3. \'Don\'t be ridiculous!\' Pat retorted angrily. “别荒唐了！”帕特生气地回答道。 4. Her roommate\'s retort made her angry. 她同屋的反驳使她生气。', '名词: retorter 过去式: retorted 过去分词: retorted 现在分词: retorting 第三人称单数: retorts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('engineering', '[ˌendʒɪ\'nɪrɪŋ]', 'n.工程学；工程', '1. That bridge was a miracle of engineering. 那座桥是工程学上的一个奇迹。 2. He is studying engineering at college. 我正在大学学习工程学。 3. Genetic engineering will have revolutionaryconsequences for mankind. 遗传工程将对人类产生深远的影响。 4. She works for an engineering company. 她在一家工程技术公司工作', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ditch', '[dɪtʃ]', 'n.沟渠；壕沟 vt.丢弃；坠入沟中；飞机（在海上）迫降 vi.挖渠；飞机紧急降落', '1. The car ran off the road into a ditch. 汽车驶离道路跌进沟中。 2. The frog jumped into the ditch. 青蛙跳进了沟里。 3. The invaders cut off their prisoners\' arms and legs and threw their mutilated bodies into the ditch. 侵略者把俘虏的四肢砍掉,然后把残缺不全的躯体扔进沟里。 4. The soldier made a dive for the ditch. 这名战士向壕沟冲去。 5. When the road becomes impassable,we have to ditch the car and walk. 道路无法通行时,我们只好弃车步行。 6. The plane had to ditch over rough waters. 飞机只能在汹涌的水面进行紧急迫降。', '过去式: ditched 过去分词: ditched 现在分词: ditching 第三人称单数: ditches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dig', '[dɪɡ]', 'v.挖；掘；翻土；探究；戳；捅 n.推；戳；挖掘；挖苦；<英口>住所', '1. Ten soldiers were told off to dig ditches. 十名战士被分派去挖沟。 2. He was buried by an avalanche and had to be dug out. 他遇雪崩被埋住了，得把他挖出来。 3. An old Greek statue was dug up here last month. 上个月在这儿挖出了一尊古希腊雕像。 4. The workmen broke up the pavement to dig up the pipes under it. 工人们把柏油路刨开，把埋在下面的管子掘了出来。 5. She gave me a sharp dig in the ribs. 轻轻的一戳就会使她禁不住要笑。', '过去式: dug 过去分词: dug 现在分词: digging 第三人称单数: digs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adequate', '[\'ædɪkwət]', 'adj.足够的；适当的；能胜任的', '1. We had adequate food for a week\'s journey. 我们有足够的食物可以做一星期的旅行。 2. He sought for an adequate solution to the problem. 他寻求解决这个问题的适当办法。 3. I hope he will be adequate to the job. 我希望他将胜任这一工作。', '副词: adequately 名词: adequacy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exceptional', '[ɪk\'sepʃənl]', 'adj.异常的；例外的；特别的；杰出的', '1. Forestry has advanced with exceptional speed. 植树造林以罕见的速度得到了发展。 2. By no means are these cases exceptional. 这些例子绝不是例外。 3. This weather is exceptional for June. 六月里这样的天气是反常的。 4. We\'ve enjoyed an exceptional run of fine weather recently. 我们这里最近天气好极了。', '副词: exceptionally 名词: exceptionality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reciprocal', '[rɪ\'sɪprəkl]', 'adj.互惠的；相互的；互补的 n.相互；互惠；[数]倒数', '1. Thus there is an important reciprocal relationship between honesty and trust. 基于此,诚实与信任成为重要的互惠关系。 2. It is mutually Beneficial and reciprocal to do this deal with the Japanese. 与日本人做这笔生意，互利互惠。 3. They show reciprocal affection to each other. 他们表达了彼此之间的爱慕。 4. Although I gave him many presents, I had no reciprocal gifts from him. 虽然我给他很多礼物, 但我没有收到过他给我的礼物。 5. I trust the reciprocal nature of our love. 我相信爱情是相互的。', '副词: reciprocally 名词: reciprocality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('approve', '[ə\'pruːv]', 'v.批准；赞成；同意；称许', '1. The city council approved the building plan. 市议会批准了这项建筑计划。 2. I presume you will approve of the plan. 我相信你会赞成这个计划。 3. You can join the class if your parents approve. 如果你父母同意，你可以参加这个班。 4. I approve of your trying to earn some money, but please don\'t neglect your studies. 我同意你去挣一些钱，可是请不要误了功课。', '形容词: approvable 副词: approvingly 过去式: approved 过去分词: approved 现在分词: approving 第三人称单数: approves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thorn', '[θɔːrn]', 'n.刺；荆棘', '1. She got her finger pricked by a thorn. 她的手指被刺扎了一下。 2. One puts on gloves before grasping a thorn cudgel. 为了要握有刺的棍子，首先得戴上手套。 3. Priestesses are immune to their own thorn effects. 女祭司不会受自己创造的荆棘刺影响。 4. And still, we choose the pain of the thorn. 我们仍然选择了那痛苦的荆棘。', '形容词: thornless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('emotion', '[ɪ\'moʊʃn]', 'n.情感；感情；情绪', '1. Love, joy, hate, fear and grief are all emotions. 爱、喜、恨、惧、悲都是情感。 2. The speaker appealed to our emotions rather than to our minds. 演讲者激发了我们的情感而不是启发我们的思考。 3. I hate this kind of cheap emotion. 我讨厌这种肤浅的感情。 4. Chopin aroused very complicated emotions in her. 肖邦的乐曲唤起了她极其复杂的感情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cafeteria', '[ˌkæfə\'tɪriə]', 'n.自助餐厅', '1. They had their lunch in a cafeteria. 他们在一家自助餐厅吃了午饭。 2. The cafeteria is on the basement level. 自助餐厅在地下一层。 3. I found him work in a cafeteria by chance. 我偶然发现他在一家自助餐厅工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ahead', '[ə\'hed]', 'adv.领先；预先；在前；向前；提前', '1. By doing extra homework, he soon got ahead of his class-mates. 他靠多做家庭作业，很快在班上名列前茅。 2. He will be ahead of others in English. 他在英语方面将超过别人。 3. Pay ahead, and you\'ll receive a discount. 若预先付款，你便可以享受折扣 4. The man on the watch cried out: \"Dangers ahead!\" 守望的人突然大喊:\"前面有危险!\"', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('two', '[tuː]', 'num.二；两个', '1. Two plus five is seven. 二加五等于七。 2. All things invariably divide into two. 事物都是一分为二的。 3. At that time he had two helpers. 当时他有两个助手。 4. The two boys decided to play truant and go fishing. 这两个男孩决定逃学去钓鱼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fable', '[\'feɪbl]', 'n.寓言；神话；无稽之谈 v.讲寓言；虚构', '1. Fables often have animals as the main characters. 寓言常以动物为主角。 2. The following passage was quoted from a well-known fable. 接下来这一段是出自一篇有名的寓言。 3. We may take the story of Job for a history or a fable. 我们可以把关于约伯的故事当作历史或者当作神话。 4. We have to learn to distinguish fact from fable. 我们应当学会识别真伪。 5. He fabled about his lot. 他编造自己的身世。', '名词: fabler 过去式: fabled 过去分词: fabled 现在分词: fabling 第三人称单数: fables');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pot', '[pɑːt]', 'n.罐；壶；一大笔(钱)；奖杯（尤指银杯）；<俚>大麻 v.把 ... 装罐；射猎；(台球)入袋', '1. Will you help me to wash up all these pots and pans? 帮我洗洗这些锅碗瓢盆好吗？ 2. She stayed up all night writing the paper with a pot of coffee at her elbow. 她熬了一整夜写论文,身边放着一壶咖啡。 3. He has earned a pot of money. 他赚了一大笔钱。', '过去式: potted 过去分词: potted 现在分词: potting 第三人称单数: pots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aloud', '[ə\'laʊd]', 'adv.出声地；大声地', '1. She sobbed aloud, not caring to restrain her grief. 她大声地啜泣，不打算遏止悲哀。 2. He groaned aloud as he started to drag himself to his feet. 他一面拖着身体站起来，一面大声地哼哼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('counter', '[\'kaʊntər]', 'n.柜台；筹码；计数器；反驳 adj.相反的 adv.与…相反地 v.反对；反击', '1. He placed the money on the counter. 他把钱放在柜台上。 2. Shoppers got into a scrum round the bargain counter. 顾客在廉价品柜台周围你争我夺。 3. The circuit is a conventional ring counter. 此线路是一个普通的环形计数器。 4. They had always had the counter effect of making him beastly. 女人总产生相反的效果，使他更像野兽。 5. He acted counter to his promise. 他的行动与他的诺言相反。 6. I counter their plan with my own. 我用自己的方案去反对他们的计划。', '过去式: countered 过去分词: countered 现在分词: countering 第三人称单数: counters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slit', '[slɪt]', 'n.裂缝；狭长的切口 vt.切开；撕裂；使成狭缝', '1. A slit skirt revealed shapely legs. 开叉的裙子暴露出匀称的腿。 2. I could see them through the slit in the curtains. 我通过窗帘的裂缝可以看到他们。 3. Her skirt has a long slit. 她的裙子上有个细长的开口。 4. A slit is provided for the coin to drop through. 狭长的口子是供投硬币用的。 5. Slit the roll with a sharp knife. 用快刀把面包卷切开。', '形容词: slitty 名词: slitter 过去式: slit 过去分词: slit 现在分词: slitting 第三人称单数: slits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gravity', '[\'ɡrævəti]', 'n.重力；庄重；严重；严肃', '1. He discoursed impressively on Newton\'s theory of gravity. 他讲述了牛顿的引力定律，给人以深刻的印象。 2. The stone rolled down the hill by gravity. 石头在重力作用下向山下滚去。 3. The force of gravity pulls things towards the earth\'s centre. 地心吸力把物体吸向地心。 4. The lunar gravity is about one-sixth that on earth. 月亮的引力大约为地球的六分之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('effect', '[ɪ\'fekt]', 'n.效应；结果；影响；印象；效果；要旨 v.使产生；引起', '1. The aspirins soon took effect. 服下的阿司匹林药片很快见效了。 2. The advertising campaign didn\'t have much effect on sales. 这些广告攻势对销售额并没有起到多大作用。 3. What is certain is that every effect must have a cause. 每一个结果都有一个原因，这是确定无疑的 4. This will have a negligible effect on the temperature. 这对温度的影响将是微乎其微的。 5. Doctors cannot effect a cure if the disease has spread too far. 假如这种疾病已扩散得厉害，医生也无法妙手回春。', '形容词: effectible 名词: effecter 过去式: effected 过去分词: effected 现在分词: effecting 第三人称单数: effects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dog', '[dɔːɡ]', 'n.狗；家伙；卑鄙的人；没用的东西 vt.（灾难等）缠住；跟踪', '1. The dog kept a vigilant guard over the house. 这只狗警惕地守护着这所房屋。 2. He is really a lucky dog. 他真是个幸运的家伙。 3. You stole my watch, you dog. 你偷了我的手表，你这个卑鄙小人 4. Her career was dogged by misfortunes. 她一生屡遭不幸.', '过去式: dogged 过去分词: dogged 现在分词: dogging 第三人称单数: dogs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sense', '[sens]', 'n.感官；感觉；意识；鉴赏力；意义；理智；道理；见识 v.感觉；意识到；理解；检测', '1. I lost my sense of taste. 我丧失了味觉。 2. I had the sense that he was worried about something. 我感觉他有心事。 3. I\'m afraid I haven\'t got a very good sense of directions, so I easily get lost. 恐怕我的方位感很差，因此我容易迷路。 4. He felt an overwhelming sense of loss. 他感到非常失落。 5. The horse sensed danger and stopped. 马感觉到了危险，于是停了下来。', '过去式: sensed 过去分词: sensed 现在分词: sensing 第三人称单数: senses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slack', '[slæk]', 'adj.松弛的；懈怠的；萧条的 n.松弛的部分；松散；淡季 vt.使缓慢；疏忽 vi.变松弛；逃避工作', '1. A rope is slack if it hasn\'t been pulled tight. 如果一根绳子没有拉紧,那它是松的。 2. She was shocked at the slack discipline in the school. 对于学校松弛的纪律她感到震惊。 3. He is slack in answering letters. 他疏于回信。 4. After intense work in the summer, we are slack off now. 夏季紧张的工作过後，我们现在放松了。 5. There is too much slack in the rope. 这条绳子太松了。 6. The driver slacked up before reaching the crossroads. 司机在驶近十字路口时减慢了速度。 7. You should slack the rope before trying to untie the knot. 解结之前你应该先将绳索放松。', '副词: slackly 比较级: slacker 最高级: slackest 名词: slackness 过去式: slacked 过去分词: slacked 现在分词: slacking 第三人称单数: slacks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loss', '[lɔːs]', 'n.遗失；丧失；损失；失败；失落；死亡', '1. The loss of her purse caused her much inconvenience. 丢失钱包给她带来了诸多不便。 2. This wounded soldier was unconscious from his loss of blood. 这名伤员由于失血过多而昏迷不醒。 3. His costly mistake resulted in severe loss. 他的严重的错误导致了重大的损失。 4. The loss of the football game stirred up much anger. 球赛的失败引起了极大的愤慨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('irony', '[\'aɪrəni]', 'n.反讽；讽剌之事', '1. The good point is that the irony fully reflected. 好的地方是反讽完全出来了。 2. Irony was widely used in the works of Kafka and LuXun. 卡夫卡和鲁迅的小说中都广泛应用了反讽的艺术手法。 3. The great irony is that despite all his explanation nobody believed him. 最具讽刺意味的是：尽管他竭力解释，可没一个人相信他。 4. After Peanuts left,I could not help thinking about this irony. 落花生去后，我总是不住的这样想这件讽刺的事。', '名词复数: ironies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chairman', '[\'tʃermən]', 'n.主席；会长；董事长 v.担任 ... 的主席(议长)', '1. The chairman exhorted the party workers to take action. 主席敦促党的工作人员采取行动。 2. In the absence of the chairman of the council,the vice chairman does duty for him. 委员会会长缺任时，便由副会长代理职务。 3. Minority of board member opposed the chairman. 董事会成员中的少数人反对董事长。', '过去式: chairmanned 过去分词: chairmanned 现在分词: chairmanning 第三人称单数: chairmans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coupon', '[\'kuːpɑːn]', 'n.息票；参赛表；票券；礼券；(购物)优惠券', '1. This coupon can be redeemed at any of our branches. 这种息票可在我们的任何分行兑现。 2. let\'s fill in a football coupon. 我们填一下足球彩票吧。 3. Coupon must be presented when ordering. 请于落单前出示此券。 4. Please remember to bring the meal coupon. 会议代表凭餐票用餐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tool', '[tuːl]', 'n.工具；用具；手段；被利用者 vt.用工具加工 vi.使用工具', '1. Don\'t injure yourself with that tool. 不要让那工具伤害到你。 2. The metal tool clanged when it hit the ground. 金属工具碰到地面时发出叮当声。 3. A vacuum cleaner is a handy household tool. 吸尘器是一种使用方便的家庭用具。 4. Tissue culture is the most important tool used in virus assay. 组织培养是用于病毒试验的最重要的手段。 5. He job is to tool accurately machine parts. 他的工作是精密加工机器零件。 6. When a user clicks and drags with the tool on the drawing area, the tool does its thing. 当用户在画图区域使用工具单击并拖动时，工具就执行操作。', '过去式: tooled 过去分词: tooled 现在分词: tooling 第三人称单数: tools');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('predominant', '[prɪ\'dɑːmɪnənt]', 'adj.主要的；占优势的；显著的', '1. The predominant feature of his character was pride. 他的性格中主要的特点是骄傲。 2. Identify any predominant architectural approaches. 明确主要的体系结构方法。 3. It is the land which makes the predominant contribution. 土地为我们作出了最显著的贡献。 4. It has been suggested that most individuals harbour one predominant dermoscopic type among their naevi. 大多数患者的痣都有一个显著的皮肤镜表现型。', '副词: predominantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('holiday', '[\'hɑːlədeɪ]', 'n.假日；节日', '1. Our holiday plans are still at an indeterminate stage. 我们的假日计划还没有确定。 2. Did you have a nice holiday? 你假期过得愉快吗？ 3. We are going to France to spend our holidays. 我们将去法国度假。 4. The best holiday of the year is Chinese New Year. 一年中最好的节日就是中国的新年。', '名词: holidayer 过去式: holidayed 过去分词: holidayed 现在分词: holidaying 第三人称单数: holidays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('protein', '[\'proʊtiːn]', 'n.蛋白质', '1. You need more protein to build you up. 你需要增加蛋白质以增强体质。 2. Try to balance your diet by eating more fruit and less protein. 多吃些水果，少摄入些蛋白质，使饮食均衡合理。 3. Pulses are a good source of protein for vegetarians. 对于素食者来说,豆类食物是蛋白质的理想来源。 4. A vegetarian gets protein not from meat but from its analogues. 素食者所摄取的蛋白质不是来自肉类而是来自近似肉类的食物。', '形容词: proteinaceous');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preside', '[prɪ\'zaɪd]', 'v.主持；任主席；统辖', '1. Mr Smith will preside over the next meeting. 史密斯先生将主持下一次会议。 2. The old professor had presided over a seminar for theoretical physicists. 老教授主持了一次理论物理学家的研讨会。 3. He will preside at the election of school officers. 他是校际选举大会的主席。 4. When the Assembly holds its meeting, the chairman shall preside over the Assembly. 会员大会召开会议时，理事长担任会议主席。', '名词: presider 过去式: presided 过去分词: presided 现在分词: presiding 第三人称单数: presides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('father', '[\'fɑːðər]', 'n.父亲；神父；祖先；创始人 v.创造；当 ... 的父亲', '1. My father and mother went for a walk. 爸爸妈妈去散步了。 2. He modeled himself on his father. 他把他的父亲作为自己的楷模。 3. Father Donovan dropped his eyes. 多诺万神父垂下了眼神。 4. Father Dan entered with a big grin. 神父丹带着灿烂的笑容进来。 5. He has fathered an idea. 他已经提出了一个想法。', '过去式: fathered 过去分词: fathered 现在分词: fathering 第三人称单数: fathers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unfold', '[ʌn\'foʊld]', 'v.展开；开放；显露', '1. The war seemed to unfold in the blink of an eye. 这场战争在眨眼间就展开了。 2. That\'s how life tends to unfold before us. 生活就是这样在我们前面展开。 3. She seemed to unfold like a strong white lily under this genial breath of admiration and homage. 她似乎在这赞赏和尊敬的真诚氛围之中象一朵白色的水仙那样猛烈地开放了。 4. A walk through town will unfold many interesting buildings. 一条穿越城镇的行道将显露很多有趣的建筑物。', '名词: unfoldment 过去式: unfolded 过去分词: unfolded 现在分词: unfolding 第三人称单数: unfolds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fall', '[fɔːl]', 'v.落下；倒下；来临 n.秋天；落下；瀑布', '1. The knife fell from his nerveless hand. 那把刀从他无力的手中落下。 2. Apples fall from the tree. 苹果从树上落下。 3. The tree fell with a thunderous crash. 那棵树轰隆一声倒下了。 4. Jobs used to disappear when the snow fell. 当雪天来临时，就业机会就会消失。 5. Food prices lowered during the fall. 秋天食品价格下降了。', '过去式: fell 过去分词: fallen 现在分词: falling 第三人称单数: falls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nose', '[noʊz]', 'n.鼻子；突出部分；嗅觉 v.嗅到；探听', '1. He quirked up his nose to make a face. 他鼻子一扬作了个鬼脸。 2. I wrinkled up my nose at the nasty smell. 我闻到那股难闻的味，皱起了鼻子。 3. The child pressed her nose against the window. 那小女孩把鼻子贴在窗户上。 4. Insert the nose of the staple remover firmly under the staple. 将起钉机的尖端牢固地插在缝合钉的下面。 5. The dog nosed out a rat. 那只狗闻到了老鼠的气味。', '过去式: nosed 过去分词: nosed 现在分词: nosing 第三人称单数: noses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('terrific', '[tə\'rɪfɪk]', 'adj.可怕的；极好的；非常的；危险的', '1. The ceiling came down with a terrific crash. 随着一声可怕的巨响，天花板塌了下来。 2. The agony of that moment was terrific. 那一刹那的痛苦是可怕的。 3. The view was terrific. 景色美极了。 4. I feel absolutely terrific today. 我今天的感觉真是好极了!', '副词: terrifically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lap', '[læp]', 'n.膝部；（衣服的）下摆；控制范围 n.重叠部分；(跑道的)一圈 n.舐；（波浪）拍打声 v.包围；（使）重叠；领先一圈 v.舔食；轻拍', '1. The child sat on its mother\'s lap. 小孩坐在妈妈的膝上。 2. For quite some time, everything fell into his lap. 好长一段时间他事事称心如意。 3. The leading car crashed midway through the tenth lap. 领先的那辆赛车在第十圈的中途撞毁了。 4. The cat lapped up the milk. 猫舔食牛奶。 5. The two pictures are made to lap over each other. 那两张画被重叠在一起。 6. The waves gently lap against the shore. 海浪轻轻地拍打着海岸。', '名词: lapful 过去式: lapped 过去分词: lapped 现在分词: lapping 第三人称单数: laps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('penetrate', '[\'penətreɪt]', 'v.渗透；看穿；穿透；了解；（情报人员的）渗透', '1. The mist penetrated into the room. 雾气渗进了室内。 2. The University Chinese training should penetrate the humanity consciousness 大学语文教育应渗透人文精神 3. Honda\'s success in penetrating Western motorcycle markets. 本田公司的成功渗透西方摩托车的市场。 4. Not many people managed to penetrate my disguise. 没有几个人识破我的伪装。', '名词: penetrator 过去式: penetrated 过去分词: penetrated 现在分词: penetrating 第三人称单数: penetrates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acid', '[\'æsɪd]', 'n.酸；酸性物质；<俚>迷幻药 adj.酸的；酸性的；尖酸的', '1. Acids react with bases to form salts. 酸与碱反应生成盐。 2. The acid burnt a hole in the carpet. 酸把地毯烧了个洞。 3. The acid has burnt a hole in my jacket. 这种酸把我的上衣烧了一个窟窿。 4. The acid in the rain slowly ate away at the stone wall. 雨水中的酸性物质慢慢侵蚀着石墙。 5. Add more sugar if it tastes too acid. 如果尝着太酸的话就多放点糖。', '副词: acidly 名词: acidness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('imply', '[ɪm\'plaɪ]', 'vt.暗示；意指；含有 ... 的意义', '1. I don\'t wish to imply that you are wrong. 我无意暗示你错了。 2. What do you want to imply? 你要暗示什么? 3. His silence implied agreement. 他沉默不语意味着同意了。 4. Cheerfulness doesn\'t always imply happiness. 快活并不总是意味着幸福。', '过去式: implied 过去分词: implied 现在分词: implying 第三人称单数: implies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bad', '[bæd]', 'adj.坏的；不好的；差的；疼痛的；严重的；有害的；腐败的；低劣的；不利的；不舒服的；不健康的 n.坏人；坏事 adv.非常；不好地', '1. Smoking is bad for health. 吸烟对身体有害。 2. In the recession, our firm went through a bad time. 我们公司在经济衰退时期历尽艰辛。 3. He\'s gone to bad since he made friends with those people. 他结交那些人后就开始堕落了。 4. Their travel plan was cancelled because of the bad weather. 因为天气不好，他们的旅行计划取消了。 5. He was for putting bad men behind bars. 他赞成将坏人关进监狱。 6. That\'s what I want, and I want it bad. 这就是我想要的，而且是迫不及待要得到的。', '比较级: worse 最高级: worst 名词: badness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nap', '[næp]', 'n.小睡；绒毛；纳普牌 vi.打盹；疏忽', '1. He was aroused from his nap by the doorbell. 他午睡时被门铃吵醒。 2. It\'s my habit to take a nap at noon. 我有个睡午觉的习惯。 3. Father always takes a nap in the afternoon. 父亲下午总要睡个午觉。 4. Every afternoon the baby takes a nap for 2 hours. 每天下午宝宝都要睡两个小时。 5. The old man napped on the porch. 那位老人在走廊上打盹儿。', '过去式: napped 过去分词: napped 现在分词: napping 第三人称单数: naps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('barbecue', '[\'bɑːrbɪkjuː]', 'n.烤肉；烧烤；烤架 v.烤炙', '1. The sunshine bodes well for our barbecue. 明媚的阳光对我们的烤肉野餐是个吉兆。 2. The rain loused up the barbecue. 下雨弄砸了烤肉野餐。 3. If you\'re not busy Sunday, we\'d love to have you both over for a barbecue. 如果你周日有空，我们想请你们俩来吃烧烤。 4. We can\'t calculate on having good weather for the barbecue. 我们不能指望着有好天气才去烧烤。 5. Now and then we like to barbecue chicken in the back yard. 我们偶而会在后院子里烤鸡吃。', '过去式: barbecued 过去分词: barbecued 现在分词: barbecuing 第三人称单数: barbecues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poultry', '[\'poʊltri]', 'n.家禽；家禽肉', '1. The poultry are being fed. 家禽正在吃饲料。 2. The farm breeds a wide range of poultry. 这个农场饲养各种家禽。 3. Poultry is rather cheap now. 现在的禽肉相当便宜。 4. There is not much poultry in the shops. 商店里禽肉不太多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cargo', '[\'kɑːrɡoʊ]', 'n.货物；船货', '1. The ship is discharging the cargo. 船正在卸货。 2. Cargo insurance is a major item of our business. 货物保险是我公司的一大项目。 3. The cargo was seriously damaged by water. 船货被水严重损坏。 4. This port handles 100 million tons of cargo each year. 这个港口每年货物吞吐量达1亿吨。', '名词复数: cargoes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reject', '[\'riːdʒekt]', 'vt.拒绝；排斥；驳回；丢弃 n.不合格产品；被拒之人', '1. He rejected their offer of a job. 他拒绝了他们给他的工作。 2. After the transplant his body rejected the new heart. 他的身体对新移植的心脏产生了排斥作用。 3. If the application is unfounded, the people\'s court shall make an order to reject it. 申请不成立的,裁定予以驳回。 4. The supermarket rejected all spotted apples. 超级市场丢弃了所有的烂苹果。 5. The factory sells some of its better rejects cheaply, but it throws most of the rejects away. 这家公司廉价出售略好一些的次品，但将大多数次品丢弃。', '形容词: rejective 名词: rejecter 过去式: rejected 过去分词: rejected 现在分词: rejecting 第三人称单数: rejects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poor', '[pʊr]', 'adj.可怜的；贫穷的；低劣的 n.穷人', '1. The poor horse looked all skin and bone. 这匹马骨瘦如柴,看起来很可怜。 2. He was too poor to buy a new coat. 他穷得无法买新衣。 3. Sparkling white wine is the poor man\'s champagne. 白葡萄汽酒算是廉价的香槟。 4. Some people may regard radio as the poor relation of broadcasting. 有些人可能认为无线电广播在广播事业中稍逊一筹。 5. Conditions in poor quarters were horrible. 城里穷人居住区条件十分糟糕。', '比较级: poorer 最高级: poorest 名词: poorness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('replacement', '[rɪ\'pleɪsmənt]', 'n.更换；接替者', '1. In addition, we supply small parts for replacement. 此外，我们还提供备用小零件。 2. The carpets are in need of replacement. 这些地毯需要更换。 3. The trolley wheels can use repeatedly with the cartons replacement. 手推车车轮可以随着纸箱的更换反复使用。 4. My secretary leaves us next week, so we are advertising for a replacement. 我的秘书下星期要走，所以我们现在正登广告招聘一位替代者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('as', '[əz]', 'adv.同样地；例如；被认为 prep.作为；如同 conj.因为；像；当 ... 之时；像 ... 一样；结果；尽管 n.阿斯（古罗马重量单位，约373克；古罗马铜币名）', '1. The ground was as white as snow with petals that had drifted down from the apple trees. 满地是苹果树上飘落下来的花瓣，地上一片雪白。 2. Many things pollute water, such as tires, trash, and plastic bags. 很多东西使水污染，例如轮胎、垃圾和塑胶袋。 3. This cathedral was regarded as a miracle in architectural history. 这座大教堂被认为是建筑史上的奇迹。 4. As a cub reporter he would learn the facts of life in the newspaper world. 作为一名初出茅庐的记者，他要了解报界生涯的内幕。 5. As the wage of the job was low, there were few applicants for it. 因为工资低,没有什么人申请这份工作。', '名词复数: asses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kilometre', '[\'kɪləmiːtər]', 'n.公里；千米', '1. The bridge is almost 2 kilometres long. 这座桥差不多有两公里长。 2. Sound travels about one kilometre in three seconds. 声音在三秒钟里大约传播一公里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('software', '[\'sɔːftwer]', 'n.软件', '1. There are many sorts of software in my computer. 我的计算机里有很多软件。 2. Some publishers are now diversifying into software. 有些出版社目前正兼营软件。 3. We deal in hardware but not software. 我们只经营硬件而不经营软件。 4. Her talk ran on developments in computer software. 她谈的是计算机软件的开发问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('apologise', '[ə\'pɒlədʒaɪz]', 'v.道歉 =apologize.', '1. I must beg to apologise for coming so late. 我来得这么晚应该道歉。 2. What does Bill say to apologise for losing the bike? 比尔丢了自行车说些什么来道歉的？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quartz', '[kwɔːrts]', 'n.石英', '1. Quartz crystal is perfectly crystallized. 石英晶体是完美的结晶。 2. Quartz crystals are seldom used in such handsets. 石英晶体是很少使用这种手机。', '形容词: quartzose');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strawberry', '[\'strɔːberi]', 'n.草莓', '1. This strawberry jam is still runny: I can\'t get it to jell. 这草莓酱还是太稀，凝结不起来。 2. All the strawberry jellies had been eaten. 草莓冻都吃光了。 3. We have different pies, such as apple, cherry, and strawberry pies. 我们有不同的派，例如苹果、樱桃和草莓派。 4. They grew strawberries in their garden. 他们在园中种了草莓。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bureau', '[\'bjʊroʊ]', 'n.局；办事处；(带抽屉的）写字台', '1. He works in this bureau. 他在这个局工作过。 2. The travel bureau is not so far from here. 旅游局离这里不远。 3. He worked in a travel bureau. 他在一家旅行社工作。 4. He picked up that bureau at a second-hand store. 这个柜子是他在一家旧货店买的。', '名词复数: bureaus');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('play', '[pleɪ]', 'v.玩；比赛；（在运动队中）担当；派...出场；带；踢；击（球）；走（棋子）；出牌；演奏；播放；扮演；假装；上演；发挥（作用）；应付；处理；掠过；浮现；使轻快地活动；（喷泉）喷涌；做游戏 n.游戏；戏剧；比赛；发挥作用；玩笑；间隙；闪烁；闪现', '1. Once he is free, he will play computer games. 只要他有空,他就玩电脑游戏。 2. The boy rushed his homework through and went out to play. 那男孩急急忙忙把作业做好,出外玩去了。 3. On Saturday France plays Rugby against Wales. 星期六，法国队和威尔士队比赛橄榄球。 4. I\'ve never played right back before. 我过去从来未当过右后卫。 5. She watched the children at play in the park. 她看着孩子们在公园里嬉戏着。', '形容词: playable 名词: playability 过去式: played 过去分词: played 现在分词: playing 第三人称单数: plays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('porcelain', '[\'pɔːrsəlɪn]', 'n.瓷器；瓷', '1. The museum displays the specimen of ancient Chinese porcelain. 这个博物馆展出中国古瓷器标本。 2. I don\'t know enough about porcelain to be able to price these plates. 我不太懂得瓷器，估计不出这些盘子的价钱。 3. The porcelain is fine and glossy. 瓷质细润。 4. There is a porcelain figure on the table. 桌子上有一个瓷像。', '形容词: porcelaneous');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spokesman', '[\'spoʊksmən]', 'n.发言人', '1. He was the spokesman for the workers on strike. 他是罢工工人的发言人。 2. This journalist distorted the spokesman\'s remarks. 这名记者曲解了该发言人的话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nation', '[\'neɪʃn]', 'n.国家；民族', '1. I was told that Spain is a romantic nation. 有人告诉我说，西班牙是个浪漫的国家。 2. The nation levied all able-bodied man for the war. 国家征召所有壮丁参战。 3. My judgement was frequently faulty, but my loyalty to the nation could not be questioned. 我的判断经常出错，但是我对祖国的忠诚是无可置疑的。 4. The Jewish nation is scattered around the world. 犹太民族散居于世界各地。', '形容词: nationless 名词: nationhood');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('important', '[ɪm\'pɔːrtnt]', 'adj.重要的；重大的；（指人）有很大影响或权威的', '1. History chronicles important events of the past. 历史记载历代重要的事件。 2. He has made an important contribution to the company\'s success. 他对公司的成功作出了重要的贡献。 3. It\'s very important to teach the children about road safety. 把交通安全常识教给孩子们是非常重要的。 4. It was one of the most important discoveries ever made. 这是所做出的最重大的发现之一。', '副词: importantly 名词: importance');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commerce', '[\'kɑːmɜːrs]', 'n.贸易；商业', '1. We must promote commerce with neighbouring countries. 我们必须促进与邻国的贸易。 2. Our country has been trying to broaden its commerce with other nations. 我国一直在努力扩大与其他国家的贸易往来。 3. In USA, NewYork City is the chief seat of commerce. 在美国,纽约是主要的商业中心。 4. Banks are the nerves of commerce. 银行是商业的中枢。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('die', '[daɪ]', 'v.死；枯竭；消失；渴望 n.骰子；印模；金属模子', '1. Nowadays many people die of cancer. 现在有很多人死于癌症。 2. Many people die from famine in Africa. 在非洲许多人死于饥荒。 3. My grandfather died at the age of 86. 我爷爷在86岁时去世了。 4. Flowers soon die if they are left without water. 如果不给花儿浇水,很快它们就会枯死。', '名词复数: dies 过去式: died 过去分词: died 现在分词: dying 第三人称单数: dies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('education', '[ˌedʒu\'keɪʃn]', 'n.教育；修养；教育学', '1. Education develops potential abilities. 教育能开发人的潜能。 2. No country can afford to neglect education. 任何国家都不容忽视教育。 3. Our teacher expounded his views on education to me at great length. 我们的老师向我详细讲述了他的教育观点。 4. He was handicapped by lack of education. 他因文化水平低而吃了亏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('carpet', '[\'kɑːrpɪt]', 'n.地毯；地毯状物 vt.铺盖；铺以地毯', '1. This carpet is of Russian style. 这块地毯是俄国风格的。 2. Our living room is covered with a carpet. 我们的起居室里铺了地毯。 3. A carpet of leaves covered the ground. 一层厚厚的落叶覆盖在地上。 4. The lawn is carpeted with fallen leaves. 草坪被落叶覆盖着。', '过去式: carpeted 过去分词: carpeted 现在分词: carpeting 第三人称单数: carpets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fine', '[faɪn]', 'adj.好的；优质的；精致的；晴朗的；健康的；细微的 adv.合适地；恰好地 n.罚款；罚金；结尾 v.罚款；优化；净化；细化', '1. She is a fine singer, as her mother used to. 像她妈妈过去一样,她是个很好的歌手。 2. She has a remarkably fine voice. 她嗓音非常好。 3. We\'re going to a famous restaurant famous for its fine cuisine. 我们要去一家有名的餐馆,它是以精致的菜肴闻名。 4. Yesterday\'s forecast reported it\'d be fine. 不过,昨天的预报说是会放晴的。 5. That suits me fine. 这对我很合适。 6. The judge imposed a fine of ten pounds on him. 这个法官让他缴纳10英镑的罚款。 7. He was fined 200 dollars. 他被罚款200美元。', '形容词: finable 比较级: finer 最高级: finest 名词: fineness 过去式: fined 过去分词: fined 现在分词: fining 第三人称单数: fines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relativity', '[ˌrelə\'tɪvəti]', 'n.相对性；相对论', '1. They teach the relativity of all ethical ideas. 他们宣扬一切道德观念的相对性。 2. To most people the law of relativity is difficult to explain. 对大多数人来说，相对性的规律很难解释。 3. Einstein put forward his new theory of relativity. 爱因斯坦提出了相对论的新学说。 4. Not everyone can understand Einstein\'s Theory of Relativity. 不是每个人都能读懂爱因斯坦的相对论的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thought', '[θɔːt]', 'n.思想；想法；意向；思念；观念；打算；关心；顾虑 v.想，思考，考虑（动词think的过去式和过去分词）', '1. The old man was lost in thought and did not hear us come in. 这个老人凝神沉思，没有听见我们进来。 2. Art is the mold of feeling as language is the mold of thought. 艺术是感情的模制品,犹如语言是思想的模制品。 3. They stood possessed by the same thought. 他们站在那儿,心里让同样的想法所盘踞。 4. The thought nerved me to make an other effort. 这种想法激励我再作一番努力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('medal', '[\'medl]', 'n.奖章；勋章；纪念章 vi.获得奖章', '1. He got a medal for bravery. 他因勇敢而获得一枚奖章。 2. She was awarded a medal for bravery. 她因勇敢而获得奖章。 3. He got a medal for his gallantry. 他因勇敢而赢得一枚勋章。 4. The soldier earned a medal for bravery. 这名战士因作战勇敢而获得了勋章。 5. Winning the medal was a feather in his cap. 获得奖章是他的荣誉。', '形容词: medallic 过去式: medaled/medalled 过去分词: medaled/medalled 现在分词: medaling/medalling 第三人称单数: medals/medals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('often', '[\'ɔːfn]', 'adv.经常；时常；屡次', '1. I often take my children to play in the park. 我经常带我的孩子们去公园玩。 2. My brother often scolds me without reason. 我哥哥经常无故责备我。 3. Judy goes to the movies as often as Sara does. 朱迪像莎拉一样时常去看电影。 4. They often went carolling at Christmas. 他们在圣诞节时常去挨门挨户地唱圣诞颂歌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cause', '[kɔːz]', 'vt.引起；使发生 n.原因；理由；事业', '1. Smoking can cause lung cancer. 吸烟可致肺癌。 2. She is always causing trouble for people. 她总是给人添麻烦。 3. Police are investigating the causes of the explosion. 警方正在调查爆炸的原因。 4. You have no cause for complaint. 你没有理由抱怨。', '形容词: causable 名词: causer 过去式: caused 过去分词: caused 现在分词: causing 第三人称单数: causes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pair', '[per]', 'n.一对；一双；一副 v.（使）成对；（使）配对', '1. These two cups will make a pair. 这两个杯子可以配成一对。 2. The newly married couple are really a happy pair. 那对新婚夫妇真是快乐的一对。 3. This pair of shoes is durable. 这双鞋很耐磨。 4. The young girl has a pair of almond eyes. 这个年轻的姑娘长着一双杏眼。 5. The teacher paired us off for the purpose of the exercise. 为了做练习，老师把我们分成一对一对。', '名词复数: pair 过去式: paired 过去分词: paired 现在分词: pairing 第三人称单数: pairs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('walk', '[wɔːk]', 'v.步行；陪...走；散步；偷走；走过 n.步行；散步；人行道', '1. I missed the bus and had to walk home. 我没赶上公共汽车，只好走回家。 2. The car\'s kaput we\'ll have to walk. 汽车坏了--我们只好步行。 3. I will walk you home. 我陪你走回家。 4. The children walk down the street hand in hand. 孩子们手拉手地在街上散步。 5. After running for two miles he got to a walk. 他跑了2公里后开始步行。', '形容词: walkable 名词: walkability 过去式: walked 过去分词: walked 现在分词: walking 第三人称单数: walks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mile', '[maɪl]', 'n.英里；海里；一英里赛跑', '1. My son hoofs a mile to school each day. 我的儿子每天步行一英里去上学。 2. It\'s not less than a mile to the station. 到火车站至少有一英里路。 3. He had come up from deep down in the water as the dark cloud of blood had settled and dispersed in the mile deep sea. 鱼深暗色的血在一哩深的海里，像云朵般地扩散开来，鲨鱼闻到血腥味便由深水中游过来。 4. He wants to better his record for running the mile. 他要提高一英里赛跑的纪录。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dynamic', '[daɪ\'næmɪk]', 'adj.动力的；动态的；有活力的；【音】力度变化的 n.动力；动力学', '1. This chapter is on the transformation of heat energy into dynamic energy. 这一章是关于热能转化成动力的。 2. The different varieties of the language are in a dynamic relationship with each other. 这种语言的不同变体间存在着动态的联系。 3. We are looking for dynamic persons to be salesmen. 我们正在寻找充满活力的销售人员。 4. A dynamic government is necessary to meet the demands of a changing society. 一个有活力的政府必须适应社会的改变。 5. They hoped it would act as a spiritual dynamic on all churches. 他们希望这对所有教堂来说都是一种精神动力。', '副词: dynamically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overthrow', '[\'oʊvərθroʊ]', 'v.推翻；打倒；颠覆；[体]高投 n.推翻；瓦解；颠覆；[体]高投', '1. They attempted to overthrow the monarch. 他们企图推翻国王。 2. They were plotting the overthrow of the government. 他们正在策划推翻政府。 3. The big Sam absolutely has the strength to overthrow Jerry. 高大的山姆绝对有力量打倒杰瑞。 4. Indeed,the day when this gigantic net is formed will undoubtedly be the day of the complete overthrow of Japanese imperialism. 实际上，日本帝国主义完全打倒之日，必是这个天罗地网大体布成之时。 5. They schemed for the overthrow of the government . 他们阴谋推翻政府。', '过去式: overthrew 过去分词: overthrown 现在分词: overthrowing 第三人称单数: overthrows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('undergo', '[ˌʌndər\'ɡoʊ]', 'vt.经历；经受；遭受', '1. This city underwent great changes. 这座城市经历了巨大的变化。 2. The castle will undergo extensive and costly renovations. 那城堡要用巨资进行全面整修。 3. Man\'s idea of God would undoubtedly undergo a change if we were to discover other intelligent beings in the universe. 如果我们真的发现宇宙中有其他的智慧生命,人类关于上帝的观念一定会经历一场变化。 4. I hope that I shall never again have to undergo such unpleasant experience. 我希望我永远不会再遭遇到这种不愉快的经历。', '过去式: underwent 过去分词: undergone 现在分词: undergoing 第三人称单数: undergoes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('amuse', '[ə\'mjuːz]', 'v.娱乐；消遣；使 ... 发笑', '1. I amuse myself by reading on weekends. 周末我读书消遣。 2. It is not always easy to amuse oneself on holiday. 让自己在假期里自娱并不总是容易的。 3. The boys amuse themselves by drawing caricatures of their teacher. 男孩子们以画老师的漫画取乐。 4. He could amuse us for hours with his stories of the theater. 他能接连几小时地为我们讲戏剧故事逗我们发笑。', '形容词: amusable 名词: amuser 过去式: amused 过去分词: amused 现在分词: amusing 第三人称单数: amuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coward', '[\'kaʊərd]', 'n.懦夫 adj.胆小的 Coward. n.科沃德(姓氏)', '1. Only a coward gives in to his fate. 只有懦夫向命运屈服。 2. He is a coward by his own admission. 他自己承认是个胆小鬼。 3. There is a coward silence when the stern principal come in. 严厉的校长走进来时,大家胆怯得不敢出声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('combat', '[\'kɑːmbæt]', 'n.战斗；试图解决 v.战斗；与 ... 斗争；试图解决 adj.战斗的', '1. The fighter planes quickly disengaged from the combat. 歼击机很快从战斗中撤出了。 2. He is stuck in the combat against this problem. 他在解决这个难题的过程中遇到了障碍。 3. The nation will combat all invaders. 这个民族将同所有的入侵者战斗。 4. The ship is combating the wind and waves. 那只船正与风浪搏斗。 5. The soldiers are ready to fly the 50 combat mission. 战士们已经准备好了执行第50号战斗任务。', '过去式: combated/combatted 过去分词: combated/combatted 现在分词: combating/combatting 第三人称单数: combats/combats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('illustration', '[ˌɪlə\'streɪʃn]', 'n.说明；插图；图解；例证', '1. He used photographs as illustration for his talk. 他用照片为他的演讲作图片说明。 2. The scientist used vivid examples in illustration of his theory. 科学家以生动的例子说明他的理论。 3. This is the common case, and requires no illustration. 这是常见的情况，无需说明。 4. The text is accompanied by illustration. 正文附有插图。', '形容词: illustrational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('answer', '[\'ænsər]', 'v.回答；答复；接电话 n.答案；回答；答复', '1. The question is simple enough to answer. 这个问题很简单,容易回答。 2. she fell into a rage and refused to answer. 他勃然大怒,拒不回答。 3. He answered that he knew nothing about it. 他答复说关于此事他一无所知。 4. He has a large amount of mail to answer every day. 他每天有大量的信件要回复。 5. Do you know the answer to this question? 你知道这道题的答案吗？', '过去式: answered 过去分词: answered 现在分词: answering 第三人称单数: answers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exile', '[\'ekzaɪl]', 'n.放逐；流放；被放逐者 vt.放逐；流放', '1. The king was sent into exile. 国王遭到放逐。 2. He was publicly disgraced and sent into exile. 他被当众贬谪，放逐异乡。 3. Everyone is born king,and most people die in exile. 每个人生下来都是王，而大多数人却在放逐中死去。 4. Exile was for him a living death. 他遭流放是进了活地狱。 5. He was exiled from the country for one year. 他被放逐一年。', '形容词: exilic 过去式: exiled 过去分词: exiled 现在分词: exiling 第三人称单数: exiles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('simplicity', '[sɪm\'plɪsəti]', 'n.简单；单纯；简朴', '1. The simplicity of the book makes it suitable for children. 这本书简单易懂，适合儿童。 2. Modern furniture design tends to simplicity. 现代家俱设计越来越简单。 3. He believes everything with childlike simplicity. 他以孩童般的单纯相信一切。 4. The monastic community generally lives a life of simplicity. 僧侣界通常过着简朴生活。', '名词复数: simplicities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reassure', '[ˌriːə\'ʃʊr]', 'v.使…安心；再保证；重拾(信心等)', '1. The police reassured her about the child\'s safety. 警察让她放心，她的孩子很安全。 2. We went to the hospital to reassure ourselves about his condition. 我们去医院查明他的病情以使我们安心。 3. The manager tried to reassure her that she will not lose her job. 经理试图使她解除疑虑,她是不会失去工作的。 4. A glance in the mirror reassured him that his tie wasn\'t crooked. 他照了一下镜子，领带确实没有戴歪。', '副词: reassuringly 名词: reassurance 过去式: reassured 过去分词: reassured 现在分词: reassuring 第三人称单数: reassures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fax', '[fæks]', 'n.传真 v.传真', '1. We receive a fax of the order this morning. 我们今天上午收到一份传真订单。 2. I was on vacation last week and didn\'t receive your fax. 上星期我正在度假，没收到你们的传真。 3. After you think it over, please let me know by fax. 你仔细考虑过之后，请用传真相告。 4. Reservations can be made by letter or fax. 可以来信或传真预订。 5. Could you fax me the latest version? 你可不可以把最新版本传真给我?', '过去式: faxed 过去分词: faxed 现在分词: faxing 第三人称单数: faxes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('foolish', '[\'fuːlɪʃ]', 'adj.愚蠢的；荒谬的；可笑的', '1. They all jeer at the foolish speaker. 他们都嘲笑那个愚蠢的演说者。 2. It\'s foolish to idle away one\'s precious time. 把大好时光浪费掉是愚蠢的。 3. He could not account for his foolish mistake. 他无法解释他所犯的荒谬的错误。 4. If fifty million people say a foolish thing, it is still a foolish thing. 假使五千万人讲出一件荒谬的事，那仍然是荒谬的事。', '副词: foolishly 名词: foolishness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('safeguard', '[\'seɪfɡɑːrd]', 'n.保卫者；保护措施 vt.保卫；保护', '1. There is no safeguard against inappropriate data types being added. 没有保护措施来防止添加不适当的数据类型。 2. We must safeguard our national interests. 我们必须保卫国家的利益。 3. To safeguard the peace is one of the important tasks of the army. 军队的重要任务之一是保卫和平。 4. Safeguard records from damage or deterioration. 保护以防记录损坏或变质。', '过去式: safeguarded 过去分词: safeguarded 现在分词: safeguarding 第三人称单数: safeguards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('affection', '[ə\'fekʃn]', 'n.影响；感情；喜爱；慈爱', '1. He\'s so susceptible that she easily gained his affection. 他易受感情影响，所以她很轻易就得到了他的爱。 2. You appear to me to allow nothing for the influence of friendship and affection. 我觉得你未免否定了友谊和感情对于一个人的影响。 3. Don\'t squander your affection on him, he\'ll never love you. 不要把感情浪费在他身上，他是永远不会爱你的。 4. He\'s so susceptible that she easily gained his affection. 他易受感情影响，所以她很轻易就得到了他的爱。', '形容词: affectional 副词: affectionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('vulgar', '[\'vʌlɡər]', 'adj.通俗的；粗俗的；乡土的 n.平民，百姓', '1. Life is a vulgar flare amid the cool radiance. 生命只是惨淡的星光里的平凡的一闪. 2. The vice premier led a vulgar life in his hometown after he resigned. 那位副总理辞职后在故乡过着平民生活。 3. Her taste in clothing is rather vulgar. 她穿着相当俗气。 4. Putting food into one\'s mouth with a knife is considered vulgar in England. 在英国，用刀把食物送进嘴里被认为是粗鲁的行为。', '副词: vulgarly 名词: vulgarness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glitter', '[\'ɡlɪtər]', 'n.灿烂；闪烁；辉耀；亮片 v.闪烁', '1. Wealth\'s glitter never washed a foul life clean. 财富的光辉永远洗不净肮脏的生涯。 2. In these cities what remains of the old China is hidden by the glitter. 在这些城市里，旧中国所遗留下来的东西都被闪烁的灯光掩埋了。 3. He stared at me with a cruel glitter in his eyes. 他眼露凶光地瞪着我。 4. She felt the glitter of the visions mounting to her brain. 这个梦幻世界放射出的华丽光辉逐渐侵入了她的脑海。 5. The diamond ring on her finger glittered in the light. 她手指上的钻石戒指在灯光下闪闪发光。', '形容词: glittery 副词: glitteringly 过去式: glittered 过去分词: glittered 现在分词: glittering 第三人称单数: glitters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reckless', '[\'rekləs]', 'adj.鲁莽的；不计后果的；大意的', '1. He\'s a reckless driver. 他是个鲁莽的司机。 2. He apologized for their reckless behavior. 他对他们的鲁莽行为道了歉。 3. His brother is a reckless gambler. 他的弟弟是个不计后果的赌徒。 4. It\'s the way you try to sound rough or reckless. 你说起话来故意这样显得很粗野或者毫不在乎。', '副词: recklessly 名词: recklessness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dismiss', '[dɪs\'mɪs]', 'vt.开除；解散；屏除；（法律）驳回', '1. If you are late again, you will be dismissed. 如果你再迟到，你将被解雇。 2. Let us dismiss and return in an hour. 让我们先解散,一个钟头后再回来。 3. We should dismiss all thought of revenge. 我们应该屏除一切报复的念头。 4. The justice dismissed his evidence out of hand. 法官当即驳回了他的证据。', '形容词: dismissible 名词: dismission 过去式: dismissed 过去分词: dismissed 现在分词: dismissing 第三人称单数: dismisses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('swing', '[swɪŋ]', 'n.摇摆；改变；冲力；秋千 v.摇摆；旋转；动摇', '1. The swing of the ship made many people seasick. 船的摇摆使许多人晕船。 2. The willow branches swing in the breeze. 柳枝迎风摇摆。 3. I used to swing, but then age and good taste overtook me. 我原来喜欢赶时髦，后来随着年龄的增长和审美观的改变便不再那样了。 4. Tiny changes here can be felt in the backswing and lead to big improvements in the hit swing. 这里在后摆时能够感受出来的很小的改变就可以让你在击球摆动上得到很大的进步。 5. This will swing public opinions against the government. 这将使公共舆论转而反对政府。', '形容词: swingy 过去式: swung 过去分词: swung 现在分词: swinging 第三人称单数: swings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('desk', '[desk]', 'n.书桌；服务台；柜台；部门；小台架', '1. There are three books on the desk. 书桌上有三本书。 2. The speaker had a sheaf of notes on the desk in front of him. 演讲者在他面前的桌子上放着一叠笔记。 3. He was rifling through her desk in a desperate search for the letter. 他拼命在她的书桌里搜寻那封信。 4. This kind of desk can be adjusted to the height you need. 这种书桌的高低可以按照你的需要调节。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mosquito', '[mə\'skiːtoʊ]', 'n.蚊子', '1. The mosquito is the disgusting thing. 蚊子是讨厌的东西。 2. Mosquitoes like to suck the blood of people and animals. 蚊子喜好吸人和动物的血。 3. The mosquito is a transmitter of disease. 蚊子能传播疾病。', '名词复数: mosquitoes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('orchestra', '[\'ɔːrkɪstrə]', 'n.管弦乐队', '1. The orchestra tuned their instruments. 乐队在给乐器调音。 2. The orchestra has several concert engagements. 这管弦乐队已安排好几场音乐会。 3. This orchestra has been established under the patronage of the government. 这个交响乐团是在政府赞助下成立的。', '形容词: orchestral 副词: orchestrally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enthusiastic', '[ɪnˌθuːzi\'æstɪk]', 'adj.热心的；热情的；热烈的', '1. He is enthusiastic about helping others. 他热心助人。 2. He doesn\'t know much about this subject, but he\'s very enthusiastic. 他对这事所知不多,但他非常热心。 3. The audience were enthusiastic on the opening night of the play. 那出戏首次公演之夜观众非常热情。 4. His idea received an enthusiastic response. 他的想法获得热烈的响应。', '副词: enthusiastically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('longitude', '[\'lɑːndʒətuːd]', 'n.经度', '1. Leonids don\'t peak over your longitude. 狮子座流星雨极大期不会在你的那个经度出现。 2. Prolong the sponge along the longitude and latitude at an altitude. 沿着经度和纬度在一高度延长海绵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drawback', '[\'drɔːbæk]', 'n.缺点；退税；退款；不利条件；弊', '1. The great drawback to living near a main road is noise. 住在大街旁最大的缺点是噪音。 2. Everything has its drawbacks. 凡事都有不足之处。 3. Many people are talking about the impact of export drawback system reform on the economy in China these days. 这些天来许多人都在讨论出口退税制度改革对我国经济的影响。 4. Illness is a great drawback to a learner. 患病对学生来说是大为不利的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alongside', '[əˌlɔːŋ\'saɪd]', 'adv.在旁边 prep.在 ... 旁边', '1. He is the master of the boat moored alongside. 他是那条靠着码头停泊的船的主人。 2. The police car pulled up alongside. 那辆警车在旁边停下。 3. The car drew up alongside the road. 小汽车在路边停下来。 4. The dog ran alongside his mistress. 狗在女主人的身边奔跑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('robe', '[roʊb]', 'n.长袍 v.(使)穿上长袍', '1. Many Arabs wear long flowing robes. 许多阿拉伯人身穿松垂的长袍. 2. She was simply dressed in a plain white robe. 她只穿了一件朴素的白色长袍。 3. In the early morning, he robed and drove abroad. 他一早就穿好衣服开车出门了。 4. He robes himself in moonlight. 他沐浴在月光下。', '过去式: robed 过去分词: robed 现在分词: robing 第三人称单数: robes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tall', '[tɔːl]', 'adj.高的', '1. The boy is 150 centimetres tall. 这个男孩身高150厘米。 2. She\'s tall for her age. 从她的年龄来看，她个子算是高的。 3. The tall hedge breaks the force of the wind . 高的树篱能减弱风力。 4. That woman wore a very tall hat on her head. 那个妇女戴了一顶很高的帽子。', '形容词: tallish 比较级: taller 最高级: tallest 名词: tallness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('autumn', '[\'ɔːtəm]', 'n.秋季；秋天', '1. The autumn or winter term start in September. 秋季或冬季学期九月份开始。 2. Autumn crops promised to be equally good. 秋季作物看来收成也会同样很好。 3. The chill of autumn is in the air. 秋天的寒意到处感觉得到。 4. I think autumn is the most beautiful season in a year. 我认为秋天是一年中最美的季节。', '形容词: autumnal 副词: autumnally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kind', '[kaɪnd]', 'adj.亲切的；善良的；仁慈的；宽容的 n.种类；本质', '1. If you ever see George, give him my kind regards. 如果你见到乔治,请代我向他致以亲切的问候。 2. Taking a blind man across the street is a kind act. 扶盲人过马路是一种善良的行为。 3. She had a very kind mother. 她有一位非常仁慈的母亲。 4. Our neighbor was very kind about the window we broke. 我们的邻居对我们打破玻璃表现得很宽容 5. We often do this kind of exercise. 我们经常做这类练习。', '比较级: kinder 最高级: kindest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tunnel', '[\'tʌnl]', 'n.隧道；地道；洞穴 v.挖地道；挖隧道', '1. The heavy traffic crawled through the narrow tunnel. 拥挤的车辆慢吞吞地穿过狭窄的隧道。 2. Suddenly the train roared into a tunnel and everything was black. 突然火车轰隆隆地驶入一个隧道，四周的一切都漆黑一团。 3. The kid dug a tunnel in the sand. 小孩在沙堆里挖了一个地道。 4. Moles make underground tunnels. 鼹鼠常打地洞。 5. The engineers had to tunnel through solid rock. 工程师须要在坚实的岩石中开凿隧道。', '名词: tunneler 过去式: tunneled/tunnelled 过去分词: tunneled/tunnelled 现在分词: tunneling/tunnelling 第三人称单数: tunnels/tunnels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('part', '[pɑːrt]', 'n.部分；零件；角色；部位 v.断裂；分离；离开；分开；不赞成 adv.部分地 adj.分离的（-前缀）', '1. This piece of glass seems to be part of a lamp. 这片玻璃似乎是一盏灯的一部分。 2. This is one of the nicest parts of San Francisco. 这是旧金山最好的地方之一。 3. He liked the feeling of being part of the team. 他喜欢成为这个队伍的一部分。 4. We\'re waiting for an auto part to come from Germany. 我们正在等来自德国的汽车零件。 5. The cable suddenly parted. 缆索突然断裂。 6. Their feelings were part excitement, part fear. 他们即兴奋又害怕。 7. The development is part-financed by the Energy Department. 部分开拓基金是由能源部提供的。', '过去式: parted 过去分词: parted 现在分词: parting 第三人称单数: parts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('psychology', '[saɪ\'kɑːlədʒi]', 'n.心理；心理学', '1. I can\'t understand that man\'s psychology. 我无法理解那个人的心理。 2. She had no personal life and no private psychology. 她没有个人的生活和隐秘的心理活动。 3. Many people failed in the psychology test. 很多人在心理测试环节被淘汰。 4. This is fluky psychology, also be pure belong to accidental. 这是侥幸心理，亦是纯属偶然。', '名词复数: psychologies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coach', '[koʊtʃ]', 'n.教练；经济舱；(火车)客车车厢；四轮马车 v.指导；训练', '1. The football coach was criticized by the local paper. 这位足球教练受到了当地报纸的批评。 2. The coach is bringing on some girls in the reserve team. 教练正教导预备队的女孩们练球。 3. Only soft drinks are complimentary in coach. 在经济舱内,只有软性饮料是免费的。 4. The coach was full so a relief was put on. 长途汽车已满员，所以增开了一辆。 5. I am coaching some people for English exams. 我为一些准备英语考试的人做辅导。', '形容词: coachable 名词: coacher 过去式: coached 过去分词: coached 现在分词: coaching 第三人称单数: coaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discourage', '[dɪs\'kɜːrɪdʒ]', 'vt.阻碍；使气馁', '1. Inflation discourages saving. 通货膨胀阻碍储蓄的积累。 2. A new law has been brought in to discourage racial prejudice. 一项反对种族歧视的新法律已被提出。 3. Try to discourage such familiarities from your subordinates. 不要让属下对你这样不拘礼仪。 4. I was never discouraged against learning English. 我从未对学习英语失去信心。', '形容词: discourageable 副词: discouragingly 名词: discourager 过去式: discouraged 过去分词: discouraged 现在分词: discouraging 第三人称单数: discourages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('boy', '[bɔɪ]', 'n.男孩；儿子；男服务员', '1. That boy is about ten years old. 那个男孩大约有十岁。 2. The stone just missed the boy. 那块石头差点儿砸到那个男孩。 3. Don\'t cry, you are a big boy now. 别哭，你现在已经是大男孩了。 4. She is partial to her youngest boy. 她偏爱她的小儿子。', '名词: boyhood');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hedge', '[hedʒ]', 'n.树篱；篱笆；障碍；防护物；套期保值；推诿 v.用树篱围；避免直接回答；两面下注', '1. They managed to wriggle their way through the thick hedge. 他们设法钻过了厚厚的树篱。 2. There is an opening in the hedge. 这篱笆上有个洞。 3. There is a hedge of spectators along the sidewalk. 沿着人行道形成了一道观众障碍。 4. Buying a house is the best hedge against inflation. 购买房子是防止通货膨胀的最佳保障。 5. Mr. Green began to hedge his courtyard in last year. 去年格林先生开始把他的庭院用篱笆围起来。', '形容词: hedgy 名词: hedger 过去式: hedged 过去分词: hedged 现在分词: hedging 第三人称单数: hedges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tentative', '[\'tentətɪv]', 'adj.不确定的；暂时的；试验性质的；犹豫不决的', '1. He still held a tentative relationship with Mary. 他还和玛丽保持着若即若离的关系。 2. Could we make a tentative appointment for Friday? 我们能暂时先约在星期五吗? 3. We\'ve drawn up a tentative program for the next two weeks. 我们制定了一个之后两个星期的试探性计划。 4. Each step he took was slightly tentative. 他每走一步都有些迟疑不决。', '副词: tentatively 名词: tentativeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('secret', '[\'siːkrət]', 'n.秘密；奥秘；秘诀 adj.秘密的；机密的', '1. Our plan must remain a secret. 我们的计划必须保密。 2. His secret died with him, for he never told anyone. 他的秘密至死也不为人知，因为他从未告诉过别人。 3. What new secrets of the universe will the new telescope reveal? 新的望远镜将会给我们展示宇宙的哪些新奥秘呢？ 4. What\'s the secret of baking perfect bread? 烤出好面包的秘诀是什么？ 5. We discovered a secret passage behind the wall. 我们在墙后发现了一个秘密通道。', '副词: secretly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('misfortune', '[ˌmɪs\'fɔːrtʃuːn]', 'n.不幸；灾祸', '1. One misfortune followed hard on another. 不幸接踵而来。 2. He had the misfortune to break his left arm. 他不幸把左胳臂折断了。 3. They bravely buffeted misfortune\'s billows. 他们勇敢地与灾祸的恶浪搏斗。 4. Falsehood is the jockey of misfortune. 谎言是灾祸的骑师。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('command', '[kə\'mænd]', 'n.命令；指挥；掌握；[计算机] DOS命令 : 引用辅助命令处理器 v.命令；指挥；掌握；博得', '1. He growled a command to her to stop. 他咆哮着命令她停下来。 2. The company commander roared his command. 连长高声发布命令。 3. He has a hundred men under his command. 他指挥一百个人。 4. The army is under the king\'s direct command. 军队由国王直接统率。 5. The general commanded his men to attack the city. 将军下令部下攻城。', '过去式: commanded 过去分词: commanded 现在分词: commanding 第三人称单数: commands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('run', '[rʌn]', 'v.跑；行驶；运转；运营；持续；蔓延；传播；竞选；遭遇；熔化；褪色；流 n.路程；奔跑；趋向 adj.熔化的；浇铸的；洄游的', '1. The little boy ran off to get his brother. 这个小男孩跑去找他的哥哥。 2. We ran into port for supplies. 我们驶进港口装补给品. 3. I can\'t make this machine run properly. 我无法使这部机器正常运转。 4. He has no idea of how to run a business. 他不知如何经商。 5. Father, please guide them to run for the course of eternal immutability. 天父啊，请您引领他们朝向永恒不变的路程奔跑。 6. The molten metal was run into a mould. 熔化的金属被倒进模内。', '过去式: ran 过去分词: run 现在分词: running 第三人称单数: runs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('restless', '[\'restləs]', 'adj.不安宁的；焦虑的；得不到休息的', '1. His father, a Virginian, was a restless man. 他的父亲是弗吉尼亚人，从不安于现状。 2. His manacled hands were restless in his lap. 他那双上了铁镣的手在膝盖上不知放在哪里才好。 3. The audience was becoming restless. 观众渐渐地不耐烦了。 4. After only a month in the job, he felt restless and decided to leave. 那工作他只干了一个月就厌倦了，决定不干了。', '副词: restlessly 名词: restlessness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('complaint', '[kəm\'pleɪnt]', 'n.抱怨；疾病；诉苦；控告；投诉', '1. You have no cause for complaint. 你没有理由抱怨。 2. You\'re always having complaints. 你一直都有怨言。 3. I have a complaint of the chest. 我胸部不适。 4. She poured out her complaints before me. 她在我面前倾诉苦衷。', '动词: complain');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('against', '[ə\'ɡenst]', 'prep.反对；逆；违背；倚靠；映衬；防御；相比；相对', '1. There are 26 votes for him and 8 against him. 有26票赞成他，8票反对他。 2. We sailed against the wind. 我们逆风航行。 3. It\'s against your promise to go on smoking. 继续抽烟,这违背了你的诺言。 4. They forced me to do things against my will. 他们强迫我做违背我心意的事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('headline', '[\'hedlaɪn]', 'n.大字标题；新闻提要；头条新闻 v.加标题于；宣扬；作主角', '1. A newspaper headline caught his attention. 报纸的大标题引起他的注意。 2. A headline on the front page draws attention to the fuller story inside. 扉页上的大字标题为的是吸引你注意里面的详细内容。 3. A bold black headline screamed out from the front page. 在头版上出现了一条令人触目惊心的粗黑体大字标题。 4. The news headlines are broadcast on the half hour. 新闻提要每到半小时正时作一次广播。 5. The newspapers headlined the story of the astronauts\' trip to the moon. 报纸大力报导太空人的月球之行。', '过去式: headlined 过去分词: headlined 现在分词: headlining 第三人称单数: headlines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('praise', '[preɪz]', 'vt.赞美；称赞 n.赞美；称赞；崇拜 vi.赞美', '1. The teacher praised her for her courage. 老师赞扬了她的勇气。 2. The guests praised the meal. 客人们称赞这顿饭做得好. 3. He deserves all the praise and worship. 他值得我们一切的赞美和崇拜。 4. He received praise from his colleagues for winning the prize. 他因获得该奖而受到同事们的称赞。 5. Mankind and womankind both like praise. 男人与女人都喜欢被赞美。', '名词: praiser 过去式: praised 过去分词: praised 现在分词: praising 第三人称单数: praises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rectify', '[\'rektɪfaɪ]', 'vt.改正；[化]精馏；[电]整流', '1. Please rectify the mistake in my bill. 请改正我帐单上的错误。 2. The captain had to rectify the compass reading. 船长不得不校正罗盘读数。 3. He cleaned the bottle with rectified spirit. 他用精馏酒精清洗瓶子。 4. Diodes are electronic devices which rectify alternating current to direct current. 二极管是将交流电整流成直流电的电子装置。', '形容词: rectifiable 名词: rectification 过去式: rectified 过去分词: rectified 现在分词: rectifying 第三人称单数: rectifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shaft', '[ʃæft]', 'n.柄；竖井；杆状物；矛；轴；（一道）光线 vt.苛刻地对待；装杆于', '1. In rotating, the shaft splashes oil up into the bearings. 当轴旋转的时候就把油溅入轴承。 2. The air flows down to a shaft and thus loses potential energy. 空气向下进入竖井，因而失去势能。 3. The horse stood between the shafts of the carriage. 马站在大车车辕中间。 4. If you bring them back to the lonely moor, you have to hit the shield three times with the shaft of the spear and then the silence of the moor will be broken forever. 如果你把这矛和盾带回到偏僻的荒野来，你必须要用矛的柄击银盾三下，这样荒野的寂静就能永远被打破。', '过去式: shafted 过去分词: shafted 现在分词: shafting 第三人称单数: shafts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('roar', '[rɔːr]', 'v.吼叫；咆哮 n.吼声；咆哮；轰鸣；喧闹', '1. He could only roar in a gruff voice. 他仅能以沙哑的声音吼叫着。 2. In the picture, the dragons and tigers won\'t roar. 图画里,龙不吟虎不啸（小小书僮可笑可笑）。 3. We roar all like bears, and mourn sore like doves: we look for judgment, but there is none; for salvation, but it is far off from us. 我们咆哮如熊，哀呜如鸽。指望公平，却是没有。指望救恩，却远离我们。 4. He roared with pain. 他疼得大叫起来。 5. The roar of the train reverberated in the tunnel. 火车的轰隆声在隧道里回荡。', '名词: roarer 过去式: roared 过去分词: roared 现在分词: roaring 第三人称单数: roars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('knit', '[nɪt]', 'v.编织；密接；结合；皱眉 n.编织', '1. She often knits while watching TV. 她常常一边看电视一边织毛衣。 2. She preferred to sew rather than to knit. 她喜欢缝纫而不喜欢编织。 3. The doctor knit the two broken bones in his arm. 医生把他臂上的两块折骨接好了。 4. The treaty knit the economies of the two nations together. 该条约把两国的经济紧密地结合在一起。 5. The son begins to knit a big fishnet. 儿子就开始编织大网了。', '名词: knitter 过去式: knit/knitted 过去分词: knit/knitted 现在分词: knitting 第三人称单数: knits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bat', '[bæt]', 'n.球棒；球拍 n.蝙蝠 v.用棒击打；拍打 v.眨眼睛', '1. He just tipped the ball with his bat. 他只是用球棒擦击来球。 2. The other boys coveted his new bat. 其他的男孩都想得到他的新球棒。 3. I want to buy a new tennis bat. 我想要买一个新网球拍。 4. The bat together with the balls was stolen. 球拍和球全被偷了。 5. Bats fly at night and feed on insects. 蝙蝠在夜间飞行，以昆虫为食。 6. Green batted for two hours on the playground. 格林在赛场上执棒两小时。 7. I\'ll be a big farmer before you can bat an eye! 他说你只要眨眨眼，我就马上变成一个富裕的庄稼人！', '过去式: batted 过去分词: batted 现在分词: batting 第三人称单数: bats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('territory', '[\'terətɔːri]', 'n.领土；领域；版图；范围', '1. The territory was carved up by the occupying powers. 领土被侵占者瓜分。 2. Each of the two countries claimed the territory. 这两个国家各自声称这片领土是自己的。 3. He seems to regard that end of the office as his territory. 他把办公室的那一头看成是他的地盘。 4. Our country is vast in territory. 我国版图辽阔。', '名词复数: territories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commission', '[kə\'mɪʃn]', 'n.佣金；委员会；委托；委任；犯罪 vt.授予；使服役；委托', '1. Do not deduct any commission from the consignment value. 不要从货物的价值中扣除佣金。 2. The report was submitted to the commission for consideration. 这份报告已呈报委员会审批。 3. He had received the commission to build a new bridge over the river. 他受委托在这条河上建一座新桥。 4. We all approve of the commission of authority to him. 我们都赞成把职权委任於他。 5. He was commissioned captain of the United States Air Force. 他被授予美国空军上校。', '形容词: commissional 过去式: commissioned 过去分词: commissioned 现在分词: commissioning 第三人称单数: commissions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('substitute', '[\'sʌbstɪtuːt]', 'n.代用品；代替者；替补队员 vt.代替；用 ... 代替；代以', '1. Water is not a proper substitute for wine. 水不是酒的适当代用品。 2. Is saccharin a good substitute for sugar? 糖精是糖的良好替代品吗? 3. We recommend this brand as a good substitute. 我们推荐的新品种可以完全替代原来的产品。 4. His friend Humboldt was his substitute. 他的朋友洪堡接替了他。 5. Only art can substitute for nature. 唯有艺术能代替自然。', '形容词: substitutable 名词: substitutability 过去式: substituted 过去分词: substituted 现在分词: substituting 第三人称单数: substitutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('symmetry', '[\'sɪmətri]', 'n.对称(性)；匀称；整齐', '1. These values constitute the symmetry waveform. 有这些数据来构成对称波形。 2. Many stems and roots show radial symmetry. 很多的茎和根都是辐射对称的。 3. His teeth spoiled the symmetry of his face. 他的牙齿破坏了他的面部匀称。 4. This addition may interfere with the symmetry of the layout. 这么一加，会破坏整个布局的匀称。', '名词复数: symmetries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heading', '[\'hedɪŋ]', 'n.标题；题目；航向 动词head的现在分词.', '1. See sections Section and Heading for more info. 更多信息请见章节和标题。 2. The heading was in large letters. 标题是用大号字母印刷的。 3. Choose a descriptive subject heading. 选择适当题目。 4. Imagine, too, that you are heading for the Arctic. 想像你正要航向北极，而且需要带五枚照明弹到达目的地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('smell', '[smel]', 'n.气味；嗅觉；嗅 v.嗅；闻；散发气味；有臭味；察觉', '1. The strong smell made me throw up. 这强烈的气味使我呕吐了。 2. The cheese was emitting a strong smell. 干酪散发出强烈的气味。 3. Dogs have a keen sense of smell. 狗的嗅觉很灵敏。 4. Hydrogen has no colour, no taste and no smell. 氢气无色、无味、无嗅。 5. Specially-trained dogs can smell out drugs. 受过特殊训练的狗能嗅出毒品。', '过去式: smelled/smelt 过去分词: smelled/smelt 现在分词: smelling 第三人称单数: smells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('composition', '[ˌkɑːmpə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.成分；作品；组织；作文；合成物', '1. We examined the rock to find out its composition. 我们检验了这一石块,想弄清它的构成成分。 2. He played many of his compositions for me. 他为我演奏了他的许多乐曲。 3. `Swan Lake\' is one of Tchaikovsky\'s best-known compositions. 《天鹅湖》是柴可夫斯基最著名的作品之一。 4. I have no idea who decided the composition of the committee. 我不知道委员会的成员是由谁选定的。', '形容词: compositional 副词: compositionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lonely', '[\'loʊnli]', 'adj.寂寞的，孤独的；荒凉的', '1. I feel very lonely without my dog. 我的狗不在旁边我就很寂寞。 2. The lonely student is starving for friendship. 那个寂寞的学生渴望友谊。 3. Living on a lonely island can be very lonely. 生活在荒凉的岛屿上会很孤独。 4. The old man lives alone in a lonely small mountain village. 那老人独自一人生活在一个荒凉的小山村里。', '副词: lonelily 比较级: lonelier 最高级: loneliest 名词: loneliness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('incentive', '[ɪn\'sentɪv]', 'adj.刺激的；鼓励的 n.刺激；鼓励；动机', '1. Haier is operating with the mechanism of Incentive Management. 海尔实行激励管理机制。 2. We should be incentive to further study in this subject. 我们应在这一课题上鼓励进一步研究。 3. To support the family is an incentive for him to work hard. 养家糊口是他努力工作的刺激因素。 4. Incentives differ from country to country and region to region and are always highest in a depressed area. 这些鼓励措施在国与国、地区与地区之间都不尽相同。一般萧条地区提供的鼓励最高。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bean', '[biːn]', 'n.豆；豆科植物', '1. Cocoa bean is used to make some kinds of drink. 可可豆用于制作一些饮料。 2. A bean grows rapidly. 豆类植物生长很快。 3. The bean plant is cultivated for animal fodder. 种植豆科植物可以用来当动物饲料。', '过去式: beaned 过去分词: beaned 现在分词: beaning 第三人称单数: beans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('frighten', '[\'fraɪtn]', 'vt.使惊吓；害怕 vi.惊吓', '1. It is illegal to frighten a pigeon. 惊吓鸽子是违法的。 2. They tried to frighten the public into obedience. 他们企图吓唬群众使他们屈服。 3. He frightened the old man into giving him all the money. 他恐吓那位老人把所有的钱都给了他。 4. You frighten me, even though you\'re gentle with me. 你使我害怕,尽管你对我很温柔。 5. You\'ll find that I don\'t frighten easily. 你会发现我不是轻易就会害怕的。', '副词: frighteningly 名词: frightener 过去式: frightened 过去分词: frightened 现在分词: frightening 第三人称单数: frightens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('demand', '[dɪ\'mænd]', 'n.要求；需求 v.要求；查问；需要', '1. Their demand is entirely justified. 他们的要求是完全正当的。 2. The demand for coal begins to slacken off in the spring. 煤的需求在春天开始减少。 3. He had the impertinence to demand a raise. 他竟冒失地要求增加工资。 4. The policeman demanded their names. 那个警察查问了他们的名字。', '形容词: demandable 名词: demander 过去式: demanded 过去分词: demanded 现在分词: demanding 第三人称单数: demands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ruthless', '[\'ruːθləs]', 'adj.残忍的；无情的', '1. The ruthless enemy killed the old lady. 残忍的敌人杀害了那位老太太。 2. To foreign observers, American capitalism looks ruthless. 对于外国人来说，美国的资本主义看起来是残忍的。 3. He\'s a ruthless businessman, as I know to my cost. 我吃了苦头后才知道他是个无情的商人。 4. Go up against ruthless street racers out to win at any cost. 不惜任何代价对赢上升对抗无情的街道叁赛者。', '副词: ruthlessly 名词: ruthlessness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('theater', '[\'θɪətə]', 'n.剧场；电影院；戏院 adj.战区的', '1. David\'s house is quite close to the Global Theater. 大卫的家离环球剧院很近。 2. I ran to the theater all along and was out of breath. 我一路跑到剧院上气不接下气。 3. The movie theater is dark on Mondays. 电影院每逢星期一公休 4. The theater was packed with children. 那家戏院挤满了小孩子。 5. American law and regulations give a theater commander a vast amount of administrative responsibility and authority. 美国的法律和规则，赋予一个战区指挥官以广大的行政责任和权力。', '异体字: theatre');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cassette', '[kə\'set]', 'n.盒式磁带；暗盒', '1. Cassette tape recorders are gradually out of date now. 现在,盒式磁带录音机渐渐过时了。 2. He bought a new cassette recorder. 他买了一台新的盒式录音机。 3. There is a little window in the cassette case so that you can see the tape. 盒式音像带上有个小窗，能看见里面的磁带。 4. I rewound the cassette and played her voice back to her. 我把录音带转回去，把她的声音放给她听。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('advanced', '[əd\'vænst]', 'adj.先进的；高级的', '1. England is an advanced industrial country. 英国是一个发达的工业国家。 2. The ancient Egyptians had advanced civilization. 古埃及人曾经拥有高度文明。 3. Our bean curd processing line is the most advanced and well- know in the world. 我们的豆腐生产线是世界上最为先进的，久负盛名。 4. The regent carried out an advanced system in his country. 摄政者在他的国家推行了一套先进的制度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('will', '[wɪl]', 'n.决心；意志；遗嘱；愿望 aux.将；愿意；必须 vt.决心；想要(某事发生)；将(财产)遗赠；规定 vi.<旧>愿意', '1. A country must have the will to repel any invader. 一个国家得有决心击退任何入侵者。 2. Free will makes us able to choose our way of life. 自由的意志使我们可以选择自己的生活方式。 3. The rich man left his son nothing in the will. 那位富翁在遗嘱中什么都没给他儿子留下。 4. She was married against her will. 她结婚是有违本意的。 5. I will do my best. 我将会尽力而为。 6. He was convinced he could win if he willed it enough. 如果他坚定决心,他确信自己可以赢。 7. Call it what you will, it\'s still a problem. 不管怎么说,这仍旧是个问题。', '过去式: willed 过去分词: willed 现在分词: willing 第三人称单数: wills 名词复数: wills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intermediate', '[ˌɪntər\'miːdiət]', 'adj.中间的；中级的 n.中间体；调解人；媒介物 vi.调解；干涉', '1. Term from the intermediate user or group. 以后的术语从中间的用户或组来计算下一个术语。 2. Intermediate arrays have porosities falling between these limits. 中间的排列方式，孔隙率介于这两个值之间。 3. I\'ve passed the intermediate level exam of Japanese. 我已经通过了日语的中级水平考试。 4. What is the structure of this intermediate? 这个中间产物的结构是怎样的?', '副词: intermediately 名词: intermediacy 过去式: intermediated 过去分词: intermediated 现在分词: intermediating 第三人称单数: intermediates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shrewd', '[ʃruːd]', 'adj.精明的；敏锐的；狡猾的', '1. Her brother is a shrewd businessman. 她兄弟是个精明的生意人。 2. It was a shrewd assessment and probably pretty close to the truth. 这个评估很有道理，可能相当正确。 3. He\'s an artist, a scientist and a shrewd businessman (all) rolled into one. 他既是艺术家，又是科学家，同时还是个精明的生意人。 4. His skill in negotiating earned him a reputation as a shrewd tactician. 他的谈判技巧使他赢得了精明战略家的名声。', '副词: shrewdly 比较级: shrewder 最高级: shrewdest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bleed', '[bliːd]', 'v.流血；渗色；榨取；放掉（水或气体）；给...抽血', '1. All the young soldiers are ready to bleed for the country. 所有的年轻战士都愿意为祖国洒热血。 2. If you cut your finger it will bleed. 如果你割破手指,那么它会流血的。 3. A page trimmed so as to bleed. 被剪裁的页次经切裁以印成出血版的纸页 4. The tax man is trying to bleed me white. 税务员正想榨尽我的血汗。', '过去式: bled 过去分词: bled 现在分词: bleeding 第三人称单数: bleeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arrest', '[ə\'rest]', 'vt.逮捕；拘留 n.逮捕；拘留', '1. The police arrested the thief. 警察逮捕了小偷。 2. You shouldn\'t arrest him without warrant. 你不能毫无根据地逮捕他。 3. The constable stop the car and arrest the driver. 警官使车停住并将司机扣留。 4. The riot led to the arrest of three young men. 暴乱导致3 个年轻人被捕。', '名词: arrester 过去式: arrested 过去分词: arrested 现在分词: arresting 第三人称单数: arrests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('astronaut', '[\'æstrənɔːt]', 'n.宇航员', '1. The astronaut can send out a robot which will work on the unknown planet, collecting rocks and minerals, putting up a permanent observation station or traveling far and wide. 宇航员可以派出机器人在这颗陌生的行星上工作，收集岩石和矿物; 建立永久性观察站，或向四面八方走动。 2. My son\'s dream is to be an astronaut. 我儿子的理想是当宇航员。 3. A rocket manned by trained astronauts will launch soon. 载有受过训练的宇航员的火箭马上就要发射了。 4. The rocket boosts the astronaut into space. 这火箭能把宇航员送入太空。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('senator', '[\'senətər]', 'n.参议员', '1. The senator spoke against the law. 这位参议员反对这条法律。 2. The senator voted to support the president. 这位参议员投票支持总统。 3. The senator addressed the gathering informally. 那位参议员非正式地向与会者发表演说。 4. The senator declaimed against higher taxes. 该参议员抨击增加税收。', '名词: senatorship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pioneer', '[ˌpaɪə\'nɪr]', 'n.先锋；开拓者；先驱 v.开辟；首倡', '1. He was a pioneer in the use of X-rays. 他是最早使用X光的人。 2. I see everybody as a pioneer out there. 我认为每个人在那里都是先锋。 3. She was descended from a pioneer family. 她来自一个早期的开拓者家庭 4. He is a pioneer in modern medical practice. 他是现代医学实践的先驱。 5. She pioneered the use of the drug. 是她最先使用的这种药品。', '过去式: pioneered 过去分词: pioneered 现在分词: pioneering 第三人称单数: pioneers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beach', '[biːtʃ]', 'n.海滩；海滨；沙滩 vt.拖(船)上岸', '1. We are basking on the beach. 我们在海滩上晒太阳。 2. They walked along the beach talking and laughing. 他们说说笑笑，沿着海滩散步。 3. They are vacationing at the beach. 他们正在海滨度假。 4. I prefer a sandy beach to a shingle one. 我喜欢沙滩，不喜欢遍布小石子的海滩。 5. He beached the rowboat in front of the cabin. 他将滑艇拖到小屋前面的岸边。', '过去式: beached 过去分词: beached 现在分词: beaching 第三人称单数: beaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('college', '[\'kɑːlɪdʒ]', 'n.学院；大学；学校；枢机主教团；社团', '1. He is studying in the theological college. 他在那所神学院学习。 2. He is at law college. 他在法学院读书。 3. He had passed the entrance examination of the college. 他已经通过了大学的入学考试。 4. Our daughter is going to college. 我们的女儿秋天就要上大学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ancient', '[\'eɪnʃənt]', 'adj.古老的；古代的 n.古人', '1. This is an ancient parable. 这是一个古老的寓言。 2. It\'s an ancient tale which appears in various guises in several languages. 那是一个以几种语言叙述的古老的故事。 3. Soldiers in ancient time used escutcheon to fight. 古代的士兵用饰有花纹的盾作战。 4. This stone axe is a relic of ancient times. 这把石斧是古代的遗物。 5. The ancients believed that the sun and moon were planets. 古人相信太阳和月亮都是星球。', '副词: anciently 名词: ancientness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Saturday', '[\'sætərdeɪ]', 'n.星期六', '1. I wish tomorrow was Saturday. 我希望明天就是星期六。 2. The concert will be given on Saturday. 音乐会将于星期六举行。 3. She goes swimming on Saturdays. 她每个星期六都游泳。 4. We will go to the cinema on Saturday morning. 我们将于星期六早晨去看电影。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('robot', '[\'roʊbɑːt]', 'n.机器人；机械呆板的人；自动机；（非洲南部）自动交通信号灯', '1. The toy robot moved forward with quick jerky steps. 玩具机器人一颠一颠地走得很快。 2. Japanese industry is making increasing use of robots. 日本工业越来越多地使用机器人。 3. The robot is a marvel of modern engineering. 机器人是现代工程技术的奇迹。', '形容词: robotic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('since', '[sɪns]', 'conj.因为；既然；自从 prep.自从 adv.此后', '1. He must have taken the book since it isn\'t here. 他一定是把书拿走了,因为书已不在这里了。 2. Since you can\'t answer the question, perhaps we\'d better ask someone else. 既然你无法回答这个问题，我们最好再问问别人。 3. He had spoken to her only once since the party. 自从那次聚会以来,他只跟她说过一次话。 4. She\'s so easily fatigued since her illness. 自从病后，她很容易疲劳。 5. Bows and arrows have long since been out of use. 弓箭很早以前就没人使用了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chronic', '[\'krɑːnɪk]', 'adj.长期的；慢性的；惯常的', '1. There is a chronic unemployment problem in America. 在美国存在长期失业问题。 2. We finally won in this chronic war. 我们终于打赢了这场长期战争。 3. My brother has chronic bronchitis. 我的哥哥患有慢性支气管炎。 4. Have you got any chronic diseases in the past? 你过去有没有慢性病?', '副词: chronically 名词: chronicity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eighteen', '[ˌeɪ\'tiːn]', 'num.十八', '1. There are eighteen students in that classroom. 那教室里有十八个学生。 2. He entered a university at the age of eighteen. 他十八岁上大学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refer', '[rɪ\'fɜːr]', 'vt.把 ... 提交；把 ... 归因；归类 vi.参考；谈及；咨询', '1. We referred the proposal to the board of directors. 我们把这一建议提交董事会处理。 2. You should refer this matter to the head office for a decision. 你应当把这事提交总部去决定。 3. He referred all his troubles to bad luck. 他将他的一切麻烦都归因于运气不好。 4. Botanists refer this flower to the rose family. 植物学家将这花归入蔷薇科。 5. You can refer to a dictionary if necessary. 如果有必要，你可以参考字典。', '形容词: referable 名词: referral 过去式: referred 过去分词: referred 现在分词: referring 第三人称单数: refers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('introduction', '[ˌɪntrə\'dʌkʃn]', 'n.介绍；引进；序言；导论', '1. There is an introduction about Norway in this magazine. 这本杂志里有一篇关于挪威的介绍文章。 2. He gave us a brief introduction about his company. 他向我们简要地介绍了一下他的公司。 3. The government saw the introduction of new technology as vital. 政府认为引进新技术至关重要。 4. The word is a recent introduction. 这个词是新传来的词。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('revise', '[rɪ\'vaɪz]', 'n.校订；修正；再校稿 v.校订；修正；校正', '1. A method to revise the radius of switch probes is also put forward. 此外还提出了一种修正开关式球测头半径的计量学方法。 2. The market turmoil has spurred economists to revise their forecasts. 当前的市场动荡已促使经济学家们重新修正自己的预测数据。 3. A method to revise the radius of switch probes is also put forward. 此外还提出了一种修正开关式球测头半径的计量学方法。 4. The market turmoil has spurred economists to revise their forecasts. 当前的市场动荡已促使经济学家们重新修正自己的预测数据。', '形容词: revisable 名词: reviser 过去式: revised 过去分词: revised 现在分词: revising 第三人称单数: revises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bless', '[bles]', 'vt.保佑；祝福；赐福；有幸具有', '1. God bless you! 愿上帝保佑你！ 2. May the gods bless this grateful heart! 愿神祗保佑这深明大义的孩子。 3. May Lord bless all of us who are in misfortune! 愿天主保佑我们这些苦难的人吧！ 4. The priest blessed the ship before it left port. 牧师在船离港之前为其祝福。', '名词: blesser 过去式: blessed/blest 过去分词: blessed/blest 现在分词: blessing 第三人称单数: blesses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('environment', '[ɪn\'vaɪrənmənt]', 'n.环境；外界', '1. She is not used to the new environment. 她对新环境不习惯。 2. We are required by environment protecting department to use anthracite. 环保部门要求我们使用无烟煤。 3. At one time, children didn\'t have to learn any more than how to cope with their physical environment. 曾经有一段时间,儿童除了学习适应外界环境以外,什么都不学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('landlady', '[\'lændleɪdi]', 'n.女房东', '1. He likes being mothered by his landlady. 他喜欢女房东无微不至地照顾他。 2. I feel at home living here. The landlady is very kind to me. 我觉得住在这里象在家里一样。房东太太对我很好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bud', '[bʌd]', 'n.芽；花蕾 vi.发芽；萌芽 vt.使发芽', '1. The roses are in bud. 玫瑰花正含苞待放。 2. Summertime bud grafting can be cut take shoot piece, or take xylem shoot less piece, in stock bine dry place decorticates. 夏季芽接可削取芽片,或少带木质部芽片,在砧木茎干处剥皮。 3. The bud developed into a blossom. 花蕾开出了鲜花。 4. The magnolia tree is in bud already. 木兰树已经长出花蕾了。 5. Trees begin to bud in the spring. 树在春天开始发芽。 6. Some flowers bud their leaves very early in spring. 有些花在春季里很早发出叶来。', '名词: budder 过去式: budded 过去分词: budded 现在分词: budding 第三人称单数: buds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slow', '[sloʊ]', 'adj.慢的 adv.慢慢地 v.放慢；减速', '1. Creeping is a slow method of progression. 爬是一种很慢的行进法。 2. The slow computer bogged us down. 速度慢的计算机阻碍了我们。 3. Business is going slow these days. 这些日子，商业活动慢慢减少。 4. My watch is five minutes slow. 我的表慢五分钟。 5. You have to slow down your car at the crossing. 在十字路口, 你得放慢速度。', '副词: slowly 比较级: slower 最高级: slowest 名词: slowness 过去式: slowed 过去分词: slowed 现在分词: slowing 第三人称单数: slows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shopkeeper', '[\'ʃɑːpkiːpər]', 'n.店主；零售商人', '1. The shopkeeper managed to keep in with his customers. 店主设法做到同顾客搞好关系。 2. She complained loudly to the shopkeeper, who answered her mildly. 她大声对店主抱怨，店主却温和地回答她。 3. I\'m sure the shopkeeper gave me short measure when she weighed out the potatoes. 我肯定那店老板给我称土豆时,扣了分量。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('latter', '[\'lætər]', 'adj.后者的；后面的', '1. I prefer the former design to the latter. 比起后者的设计方案,我更喜欢前者的。 2. One can travel there by ship or plane. Most people choose the latter. 乘船或乘飞机都可以到那,人们多选择后者。 3. The latter point is the most important. 后面提及的那一点是最重要的。 4. In the latter years of his life he lived alone and never welcomed visitors. 他晚年独居，从不欢迎来访者。', '副词: latterly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('repetition', '[ˌrepə\'tɪʃn]', 'n.重复；反复', '1. You should avoid unnecessary repetition. 你应避免不必要的重复。 2. We must avoid the repetition of a mistake. 我们必须避免犯同样的错误。 3. The story loses a great deal in repetition. 这个故事由于反复讲述而大为减色了。 4. The perfomance improved with each repetition. 演出每演一场都有改进。', '形容词: repetitional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cemetery', '[\'seməteri]', 'n.墓地', '1. He was buried in this cemetery. 他被安葬在这个公墓里。 2. They buried the urn in the cemetery. 他们将骨灰瓮埋在了公墓里。 3. His remains were shipped back and laid away in a cemetery. 他的遗体被运回，埋葬在一个公墓里。', '名词复数: cemeteries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rubber', '[\'rʌbər]', 'n.橡胶；橡皮；橡胶制品 adj.橡胶的', '1. Oil and grease will rot the rubber of your tyres. 油污能腐蚀轮胎橡胶。 2. My classmate borrowed my rubber and forgot to return it. 我的同学借了我的橡皮忘了还。 3. She used a rubber band to tie her hair. 她用一根橡皮筋扎头发。 4. Rubber boots are impervious to water. 橡胶鞋是防水的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feudal', '[\'fjuːdl]', 'adj.封建的；封地的', '1. She lost faith in feudal traditions. 她不再相信封建的老一套了。 2. He lost faith in feudal traditions. 他不再相信封建的老一套了。 3. The feudal barons were cruel to the people. 封建贵族对人民很残酷。 4. The way some landlords treat their tenants today still seems feudal. 今天有些地主仍以近乎封建的方式对待佃户。', '副词: feudally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('solitary', '[\'sɑːləteri]', 'adj.孤独的；独立的；单个的；唯一的；荒凉的 n.隐士；单独禁闭', '1. His childhood was repressed and solitary. 他的童年是压抑而孤独的。 2. The trapper leads a solitary life in the mountains. 那个设陷阱捕猎的人孤独地生活在山里。 3. Solitary as their lives were, is there no one person who would serve my purpose? 尽管他们过的是遗世独立的生活，难道就没有一个能够对我的计划有帮助的人吗? 4. A solitary rider was seen in the distance. 远处有个孤零零的骑马的人。', '副词: solitarily 名词: solitariness 名词复数: solitaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spit', '[spɪt]', 'n.唾液；小雨；烤肉叉；海峡；酷似；彻底的擦洗 v.吐口水；吐出；厉声说出；下小雨；(指火、熬热的油脂等)毕剥作响；用烤肉叉叉住；彻底地擦洗设备', '1. Mary\'s spit flew as she shouted. 玛丽喊叫时唾沫四溅。 2. Because there is spit on highland. 因为高原上下着小雨。 3. The beefis roasting nicely on the spit. 这块牛肉在烤肉叉上烤得很好。 4. The child is the very spit of his father. 这孩子长得活象他父亲。 5. The boys were spitting out of the train window. 那些男孩子向火车窗外吐口水。', '过去式: spat/spit 过去分词: spat/spit 现在分词: spitting 第三人称单数: spits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exclusive', '[ɪk\'skluːsɪv]', 'adj.排外的；独占的；唯一的；完整的；奢华的 n.独家新闻；独权', '1. He is part of an exclusive social circle and belongs to an exclusive club. 他所处的社交圈子很排外，而且参加的又是个很排外的社团。 2. The interview is exclusive to this magazine. 本杂志得到独家访问权。 3. Painting has not been her exclusive occupation. 绘画并非她唯一的职业. 4. The teacher tried to gain the students\' exclusive attention. 老师努力试着获得学生的全部注意力。 5. Everyone was surprised by the Times exclusive about the prince\' marriage. 泰晤士报关于王子大婚的独家新闻令很多人惊奇不已。', '副词: exclusively 名词: exclusiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('middle', '[\'mɪdl]', 'adj.中等的；中间的；中期的 n.中间 vt.放在中间；把 ... 对折', '1. There are 300 students or so in this middle school. 这所中学大约有300个学生。 2. He was not much above the middle height. 他不过中等身材。 3. He made a bid for middle class support. 他努力试图得到中产阶级的支持。 4. The man has reached middle age. 这人已到了中年。 5. The sheets have worn thin in the middle. 床单的中间部分磨薄了。 6. Uruguay and Haiti hung uncertainly in the middle. 乌拉圭和海地则在中间摇摆。', '过去式: middled 过去分词: middled 现在分词: middling 第三人称单数: middles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('responsibility', '[rɪˌspɑːnsə\'bɪləti]', 'n.责任；职责；责任心', '1. It\'s my responsibility to lock the doors. 我负责锁门。 2. You can\'t retreat from the responsibility in this affair. 你不能回避在这一事件中的责任。 3. The prescription of drugs is a doctor\'s responsibility. 开药方是医生的职责。 4. He is free from any sense of responsibility. 他丝毫没有责任感。', '名词复数: responsibilities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('push', '[pʊʃ]', 'v.推；按；挤；逼迫；催促 n.推；奋力；决心', '1. The little boy pushed the door open. 小男孩把门推开了。 2. They jeep is too heavy for him to push. 吉普车太重,他推不动。 3. You may push this button to call the elevator. 你可以按这个按钮叫电梯。 4. We had to push our way through the crowd. 我们得从人群中挤过去。 5. He opened the door with one push. 他一推门就开了。', '过去式: pushed 过去分词: pushed 现在分词: pushing 第三人称单数: pushes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recognize', '[\'rekəɡnaɪz]', 'vt.承认；认出；意识到；表示感激；识别', '1. His thorough knowledge and competence were recognized. 他的渊博的学识和工作能力得到了承认。 2. I recognize your right to ask that question. 我承认你有权提出这个问题。 3. Can you recognize her from this picture? 你能从这张照片中认出她吗？ 4. He has the good sense to recognize a good man. 他真是慧眼识真才。', '形容词: recognizable 副词: recognizably 名词: recognizer 过去式: recognized 过去分词: recognized 现在分词: recognizing 第三人称单数: recognizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thirst', '[θɜːrst]', 'vi.渴望；渴求；口渴 n.口渴；渴望', '1. On these dry days, you soon thirst for a cool drink. 在那些干旱的日子里，你不久就会渴望喝点清凉的东西。 2. These young children thirst for knowledge. 这些孩子们都渴求知识。 3. The cold water appeased his thirst. 凉水缓解了他的口渴。 4. Iced tea will quench your thirst on hot days. 冰镇茶在热天将解除你的口渴。 5. I satisfied my thirst with a glass of water. 我喝了一杯水解渴。', '名词: thirster 过去式: thirsted 过去分词: thirsted 现在分词: thirsting 第三人称单数: thirsts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('procession', '[prə\'seʃn]', 'n.队伍；行列 v.列队行进', '1. They watched the procession go past. 他们观看游行队伍经过。 2. The royal procession will be televised. 国王的仪仗行列将由电视播送。 3. The funeral procession choked up Lorna. 那送葬行列使洛娜流下了眼泪。 4. There was a bomb scare during the procession. 在列队行进时因怀疑有炸弹而引起恐慌。', '过去式: processioned 过去分词: processioned 现在分词: processioning 第三人称单数: processions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('game', '[ɡeɪm]', 'n.游戏；运动会；比赛；一场比赛；比赛得分；猎物；花招 v.赌博 adj.勇敢的；乐意的；跛的', '1. All the children partook in the game. 所有孩子都参加了游戏。 2. I found a computer game to divert the children. 我发现了一种供孩子娱乐的电脑游戏。 3. He is my main rival in the game. 他是我运动会上的主要对手。 4. He is expected to win the game with ease. 预计他在比赛中会轻易获胜。 5. It\'s a pity he games so deep. 他如此沉溺于赌博,真遗憾。 6. She put up a game fight against her detractors. 她勇敢对抗那些诽谤她的人。', '副词: gamely 比较级: gamer 最高级: gamest 名词: gameness 过去式: gamed 过去分词: gamed 现在分词: gaming 第三人称单数: games');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aunt', '[ænt]', 'n.伯母；姑；婶；姨', '1. She has no relations besides an aged aunt. 她除了有一个年老的伯母以外，再没有亲戚了。 2. My aunt gave me one of her brooches as a keepsake. 我姑母把她的一支胸针送给我作记念。 3. I\'m duty bound to visit my old aunt. 我有义务去探望年老的姑妈。 4. He was being terribly friendly to Aunt Liu. 这天他对刘大婶婶态度特别友好。', '名词: aunthood');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dish', '[dɪʃ]', 'n.盘；碟；一道菜；菜肴；碟状物 vt.使成碟状；装盘 vi.闲谈', '1. The careless waiter dropped the dish onto the ground. 那个粗心的侍者把盘子摔到了地上。 2. That dish is too shallow to serve soup in. 那只盘子太浅了，不能盛汤。 3. This glass dish is very fragile. 这玻璃碟子十分易碎。 4. He knows the recipe for this dish. 他知道这道菜的烹饪方法。 5. She asked Mary to help her dish up the dinner. 她要玛丽帮她把菜肴分盛到盘子里。 6. That salesman could really dish it out. 那个推销员确实能说会道。', '过去式: dished 过去分词: dished 现在分词: dishing 第三人称单数: dishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interfere', '[ˌɪntər\'fɪr]', 'vi.干涉；妨碍', '1. Don\'t interfere with my business. 不要干涉我的事情。 2. Constant interruptions interfere with my work. 一次又一次的干扰妨碍我的工作。 3. Don\'t allow pleasure to interfere with duty. 不要让娱乐妨碍了职责。', '副词: interferingly 名词: interferer 过去式: interfered 过去分词: interfered 现在分词: interfering 第三人称单数: interferes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thigh', '[θaɪ]', 'n.大腿', '1. \"The pain runs from the small of my back right down my left thigh, \" he told the doctor. 他告诉医生说：\"从后腰一直到左大腿都疼得很。\" 2. I walked the last six miles in water up to my thighs. 我在深及大腿的水中走完了最后6英里。 3. The arm is no match for the thigh. 胳膊扭不过大腿。 4. He complained about a pain in his right thigh. 他抱怨着右大腿上的疼痛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('northern', '[\'nɔːrðərn]', 'adj.北部的；北方的；有北方特征的', '1. That\'s a large city in northern Greece. 那是希腊北部的一个大城市。 2. The people of northern Canada are called Inuit. 加拿大北部的人称为因纽特人。 3. The United Kingdom consists of Great Britain and Northern Ireland. 联合王国由大不列颠和北爱尔兰组成。 4. She has travelled in northern countries. 她曾游历过北方诸国。', '名词: Northernness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('neither', '[\'niːðər]', 'pron.两者都不 adj.两者都不的 adv.也不 conj.也不；既不', '1. Neither of my parents enjoys music. 我父母都不喜欢音乐。 2. Neither of the statements is true. 两种说法都不正确。 3. He tasted both cakes and said that neither was delicious. 他两块蛋糕都尝了尝,觉得都不好吃。 4. Neither side is willing to make a move. 双方都不愿采取行动。 5. He hasn\'t got a ticket and neither have I. 他没有票，我也没有。 6. A good watch neither gains nor loses. 好表不快也不慢。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('able', '[\'eɪbl]', 'adj.能够的；有能力的；能干的', '1. We shall be able to deal with all sorts of problem. 我们应该能够应付各种困难。 2. She bet me 20 that I wouldn\'t be able to give up smoking. 她和我打20英镑的赌，说我戒不了烟。 3. Free will makes us able to choose our way of life. 自由的意志使我们可以选择自己的生活方式。 4. By no means was he able to handle it. 这件事他绝对没办法处理。', '副词: ably 比较级: abler 最高级: ablest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poster', '[\'poʊstər]', 'n.海报；装饰画；急行旅人', '1. The lettering on the poster is very eye-catching. 海报上的字体非常醒目。 2. The poster only stayed up a few hours before it was stolen. 那张海报贴上去没几个小时就让人给偷走了。 3. He put up a poster advertising the circus. 他贴了一张宣传马戏团的海报。 4. The poster wouldn\'t stick even though I drenched it with glue. 我涂了大量胶水，可那张海报就是贴不住。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inhabitant', '[ɪn\'hæbɪtənt]', 'n.居民', '1. Every inhabitant here has an obligation to pay taxes. 这里的每一位居民都有纳税的义务。 2. The inhabitant can see the Church House and the Death House， but never the exterior of the Court House. 居民也能看到教会安置和死囚刑前的住房，但从未见过法院的外貌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hope', '[hoʊp]', 'v.希望；期望；盼望 n.希望', '1. I hope to announce the winner shortly. 我希望马上宣布胜利者的名字。 2. After these dry days, everyone hopes for rain. 干燥的天气之后，人人都希望下雨。 3. I hope he will be adequate to the job. 我希望他将胜任这一工作。 4. And hope is what Yad Vashem is all about! 而盼望正是大屠杀纪念馆的主旨。 5. The doctors held out no hope of recovery. 医生们对痊愈不抱希望。', '名词: hoper 过去式: hoped 过去分词: hoped 现在分词: hoping 第三人称单数: hopes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('undo', '[ʌn\'duː]', 'v.解开；松开；取消', '1. Would you please undo this knot for me? 你能不能帮我把这个结解开？ 2. He tried to undo the knot by picking at it with his fingers. 他用手指不停地扯，想把绳结解开。 3. To return a database to its state as of the last committed change, i.e., to undo recent uncommitted changes. 使一个数据库返回到它上次已确认的改变之后的状态，即取消最近的尚未确认的变动。 4. A compensating transaction means that a new transaction will undo the effects of previous transactions. 补偿事务的意思是一个新事物会用于取消前一个事务的所有效果。', '名词: undoer 过去式: undid 过去分词: undone 现在分词: undoing 第三人称单数: undoes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bulk', '[bʌlk]', 'n.体积；容积；大块；大部分；大批 adj.散装的；大量的 vt.使膨胀；使成堆 vi.膨胀；显得重要', '1. It\'s not their weight that makes these sacks hard to carry, it\'s their bulk. 这些袋子难以搬运,倒不是因为重而是体积太大。 2. He heaved his huge bulk out of the chair. 他挺起巨大的身躯，从椅子上站了起来。 3. The bulk of the work has already been done. 大部分工作已经完成。 4. The great bulk of necessary work can never be anything but painful. 大量必须做的工作真令人痛苦。 5. We can manage some bulk carrier within two week. 我们可在两周内安排一些散装船去。 6. A dozen petticoats bulked out her figure. 十几条衬裙把她的身体撑得圆鼓鼓的。 7. The cake bulked up. 蛋糕发起来了。', '过去式: bulked 过去分词: bulked 现在分词: bulking 第三人称单数: bulks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transistor', '[træn\'zɪstər]', 'n.晶体管；晶体管收音机', '1. He devises a new type of transistor. 他发明了一种新的晶体管。 2. We must give great care upon transistor biasing. 我们必须十分重视晶体管的偏置。 3. The old man always carries about a transistor. 这位老人总是随身携带一台晶体管收音机。 4. This transistor has two batteries. 这个晶体管收音机有两块电池。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('steak', '[steɪk]', 'n.牛排', '1. I want my steak well-done. 我要全熟的牛排。 2. I would like some steak and bread. 我要牛排和面包。 3. The steak was so tough that I couldn\'t eat it. 牛排太老了,我咬不动它。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('letter', '[\'letər]', 'n.信；字母 v.写下；印刷 n.租赁人', '1. She balled the letter into a wad. 她将信揉成一团。 2. I acknowledged her letter at once. 我马上告知收到了她的信。 3. The kids are learning to trace the letter. 孩子们学描字母。 4. Anger is one letter away from danger. 生气与危险仅相差一个字母。 5. He wrote these words after he had lapped up his letter. 他是把信折好以后才又写下了这些话的。', '名词: letterer 过去式: lettered 过去分词: lettered 现在分词: lettering 第三人称单数: letters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alarm', '[ə\'lɑːrm]', 'n.警报；警报器；惊恐 vt.警告；使惊恐；向 ... 报警', '1. The proceedings were interrupted by the fire alarm. 会议的进程被火灾警报打断了。 2. The instant they heard the alarm, they fell in for action. 他们一听到警报，就立即集合准备战斗。 3. The smoke triggered off the alarm. 这些烟把警报器触响了。 4. In case of fire, ring the alarm bell. 如遇失火，请按警铃。 5. Alarm everyone quickly because the house is full of smoke. 快警告大家,屋子理都是烟。', '副词: alarmingly 过去式: alarmed 过去分词: alarmed 现在分词: alarming 第三人称单数: alarms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('profound', '[prə\'faʊnd]', 'adj.深奥的；渊博的；极度的；意义深远的', '1. Beauty is but superficial while mind is profound. 美貌是肤浅的,而思想才是深邃的。 2. I was impressed by his devotion to his research but I didn\'t have the slightest interest in his profound theories. 给我留下了很深印象,但我对他那些深奥的理论丝毫不感兴趣。 3. Our professor is a man of profound learning. 我们的教授是一个学识渊博的人。 4. Reading makes a full man, meditation a profound man, discourse a clear man. 阅读培养学问丰富的人,思考培养见识深刻的人,演讲培养思路清晰的人。', '副词: profoundly 比较级: profounder 最高级: profoundest 名词: profoundness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rug', '[rʌɡ]', 'n.地毯；毯子；旅行毯', '1. Look at the holes that have been worn in this rug. 瞧瞧这块小地毯上磨出的洞。 2. I slid the rug in front of the fire. 我挪了挪铺在炉前的地毯。 3. Bind the edge of the rug so that it won\'t ravel. 给地毯镶个边以免开线。 4. The rug singed because it was too near the fire. 地毯太靠近壁炉已烤焦了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overcome', '[ˌoʊvər\'kʌm]', 'vt.战胜；克服；使受不了；(感情等)压倒 vi.获胜；赢', '1. I realized that there is no way I can overcome it. 我意识到自己没有办法战胜它。 2. There will be no difficulty in the world that they cannot overcome. 世界上任何困难他们都可以克服。 3. We can and must overcome our shortcomings. 我们能够而且必须克服我们的缺点。 4. He was overcome by the gas fumes. 汽油味使他受不了。 5. We shall overcome! 我们一定胜利！', '过去式: overcame 过去分词: overcome 现在分词: overcoming 第三人称单数: overcomes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('newspaper', '[\'nuːzpeɪpər]', 'n.报纸；新闻纸', '1. He unfurled the newspaper and began to read. 他展开报纸开始阅读。 2. I learned this news from the newspaper. 我从报纸上得知这个消息。 3. Only when he read the newspaper did he know the story. 他看了报纸后才知道那则报导。 4. His name leapt out at me from the newspaper. 报纸上他的名字一下子跳入我的眼帘。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ward', '[wɔːrd]', 'n.病房；行政区；监护；守卫；受监护人 vt.守护；躲开', '1. The hospital has a medical ward and a surgical ward. 这医院有内科病房和外科病房。 2. The patient lay quietly on his bed in the medical ward. 病人安静地躺在内科病房的床上。 3. There are two nurses in the ward. 病房里有两个护士。 4. They phoned to every ward and suburb. 他们给各城区和郊区打电话。 5. The soldiers warded over the city. 士兵们守护着这座城市。', '过去式: warded 过去分词: warded 现在分词: warding 第三人称单数: wards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('at', '[ət]', 'prep.在；向；达 n.基普(老挝货币基本单位)(=att)；[化]砹(极不稳定放射性元素) abbr.密封的(=airtight) abbr.气温(=air temperature)', '1. I\'m sorry to obtrude on you at such a time. 我很抱歉在这个时候打扰你。 2. She had her hair styled at the beauty parlor. 她的头发是在美容院做的。 3. Snipers shot at the invaders from the roof tops. 狙击手从房顶上向侵略者射击。 4. She makes eyes at the handsome young man. 她向那位英俊的小伙子送秋波。', '名词复数: at');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interview', '[\'ɪntərvjuː]', 'n.面谈；会见；面试；接见 vt.接见；采访；对 ... 进行面试 vi.面试；采访', '1. How was your interview with Michigan? 你跟密歇根大学的人面谈得如何? 2. He mentioned that problem at our interviews. 他在我们会谈时提到了那个问题。 3. I think I fared quite well in the interview. 我觉得我这次面试考得不错。 4. May I make a few preliminary remarks before we start the interview? 在我们开始面试之前，我先说几句话可以吗？ 5. In the prosecution of his duties, he had to interview people of all classes. 在履行职责的时候，他得会见各个阶级的人。 6. I\'m interviewing all this afternoon. 今天整个下午我都要进行面试。', '形容词: interviewable 名词: interviewee 过去式: interviewed 过去分词: interviewed 现在分词: interviewing 第三人称单数: interviews');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('turnover', '[\'tɜːrnoʊvər]', 'n.营业额；流动；成交量；翻覆；半圆卷饼 adj.可翻转的', '1. The firm has an annual turnover of 75 million. 这家公司的年营业额为7500万英镑。 2. The shop has a turnover of 500,000 dollar a week. 该店营业额为每周五十万元。 3. They have a very high turnover of staff. 他们的职员更换很快。 4. Why does your company have such a rapid turnover of staff? 贵公司人员变动为什么这么快?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('implement', '[\'ɪmplɪmənt]', 'n.工具；器具；当工具的物品 vt.实施；执行；向 ... 提供工具(或手段)', '1. What implements are needed for gardening? 园艺需要些什么工具？ 2. That implement is useful for many purposes in the kitchen. 那种工具在厨房里有许多用途。 3. The system can preferably implement automatic text categorization for Chinese pages, and has a higher quality. 该系统可以很好地实现一个中文网页的自动分类，且系统中的分类器具有较高的分类质量。 4. Her designs will be put on ice until money is available to implement them. 她的设计将暂时搁起来，等有了钱再去实施。', '名词: implementation 过去式: implemented 过去分词: implemented 现在分词: implementing 第三人称单数: implements');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quota', '[\'kwoʊtə]', 'n.限额；配额；定额；最低票数', '1. Why is my Daily Resultb Quota so sall? 为什么我的每日工作限额那么小？ 2. Calculate the total Sentence Quota of the summary. 计算出摘要应包含的句子的限额。 3. The committee reversed its decision on import quota. 委员会取消了对进口货物的配额的决定。 4. The quota on import cars has been lifted. 对汽车的进口配额已被取消。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('per', '[pər]', 'prep.每；每一；经过；按照', '1. These apples cost five yuan per kilogram. 这些苹果每公斤五元。 2. We were bowling along (the motorway) at seventy miles per hour. 我们以每小时七十英里的速度(在高速公路上)飞驰。 3. The vessel tax of anchorage is 5,000 dollars per year. 这艘船的停泊税一年是五千美元。 4. Tickets to the concert are $50 per head! 这场音乐会的门票价格是每人五十美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whale', '[weɪl]', 'n.鲸 vi.捕鲸 v.打击', '1. We may live to see the extinction of the whale. 人类或许能亲眼见到鲸的灭绝。 2. The whale thrashed the water with its tail. 那条鲸鱼不住地用尾巴击水。 3. The blue whale is the world\'s largest living animal. 蓝鲸是当今最大的动物。 4. He used to whale me when he was sober and could get his hands on me. 他从前没喝醉的时候，只要能抓住我，总要打我一通。', '过去式: whaled 过去分词: whaled 现在分词: whaling 第三人称单数: whales');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('door', '[dɔːr]', 'n.门；门口；途径', '1. He chiseled a hole in the door to fit a new lock. 他在门上凿了个孔，以便装一把新锁。 2. Somebody opened the door and the candle blew out. 有人打开了门，蜡烛随之被吹灭了。 3. He sprang up and rushed to the door. 他跳起身，跑到门口。 4. He made for the door and tried to escape. 他向门口走去，企图逃跑。', '形容词: doorless 过去式: doored 过去分词: doored 现在分词: dooring 第三人称单数: doors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('faith', '[feɪθ]', 'n.信仰；信念；信任', '1. Christians profess their faith when they say the Creed. 基督教徒在念信经时就表明了他们的宗教信仰。 2. Missionaries went far afield to propagate their faith. 传教士到远方去传播其信仰。 3. The disaster caused him to waver in his faith. 这件灾难使他对信仰发生了动摇。 4. He has great talent, but he has lost his faith. 他很有天赋，但是他已经丧失了信心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fade', '[feɪd]', 'v.逐渐消失；褪色；凋谢 n.淡入；淡出', '1. Hopes of a peaceful settlement are now fading. 和平解决的希望正在消失。 2. The closing music fades out when the hero rides off into the sunset. 当男主角策马向夕阳驰去时，尾声音乐逐渐消失。 3. As evening came the coastline faded into darkness. 夜晚来临，海岸线融入茫茫夜色中。 4. These sunproof curtains will not fade . 这些耐晒的窗帘不褪色。 5. They\'ll fade in to an outdoor scene. 他们将淡入至户外的一个场景。', '过去式: faded 过去分词: faded 现在分词: fading 第三人称单数: fades');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('key', '[kiː]', 'n.键；关键；钥匙；答案 adj.关键的；主要的 vt.键入；用钥匙锁上；为 ... 调音', '1. He is striking the key of his typewrite. 他敲打着打字机的字键。 2. To exit from this page, press the return key. 退出本页面按返回键。 3. The key here is to set up a responsibility system. 关键是建立责任制。 4. This was the key to success of our initial talks. 这就是我们当初会谈取得成功的关键所在。 5. They zeroed in on the key issues. 他们集中讨论了关键问题。 6. She keyed in all the new data. 她键入了所有的新数据。', '名词复数: keys 过去式: keyed 过去分词: keyed 现在分词: keying 第三人称单数: keys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('counsel', '[\'kaʊnsl]', 'n.劝告；建议；诉讼律师 v.提供建议；劝告', '1. Good counsel has no price. [谚]忠言无价。 2. Listen to the counsel of your elders. 听从长辈的劝告吧. 3. Each side of a case in court has its own counsel. 法庭上原告和被告双方都有各自的律师。 4. The court heard counsel for both sides. 法庭听取了双方律师的陈述. 5. Most experts counsel caution in such cases. 大多数专家建议在这样的情况下要谨慎从事。', '过去式: counseled/counselled 过去分词: counseled/counselled 现在分词: counseling/counselling 第三人称单数: counsels/counsels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('odor', '[\'oʊdə]', 'n.气味；名声；气息', '1. The flowers gave off a fragrant odor. 花发出一阵幽香。 2. The odor penetrated the whole room. 整个房间里弥漫着这种气味。 3. The penetrating odor of garlic soon filled the entire apartment. 大蒜刺鼻的气味很快就弥散了整个屋子 4. What he had done put him in better odor. 他的所作所为使他的名声得到改善。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wagon', '[\'wæɡən]', 'n.四轮马车；货车 v.用四轮马车运', '1. He harnessed the horse to a wagon. 他把马套到四轮马车上。 2. An ox pulls a wagon into the village. 有只牛拉着一台四轮车进入村庄。 3. The old wagon rattled down the road. 破旧的四轮运货马车喀嚓喀嚓地行进在路上。 4. His wagon was smashed into kindling wood. 他的货车撞得稀烂。 5. They wagoned the goods to the market. 他们用四轮马车把货物运到市场。', '过去式: wagoned 过去分词: wagoned 现在分词: wagoning 第三人称单数: wagons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recite', '[rɪ\'saɪt]', 'vt.背诵；朗诵；叙述；列举 vi.背诵；回答问题', '1. Can you recite the Ten Commandants? 你能背诵十诫吗？ 2. I like to recite his poetical works. 我喜欢背诵他的诗。 3. She can recite the whole poem from memory. 她能背诵全诗。 4. Politicians recite their liturgies in TV studios. 政客们在电视演播室里朗诵祷文。 5. I don\'t like reciting in public. 我不喜欢当众朗诵。', '名词: reciter 过去式: recited 过去分词: recited 现在分词: reciting 第三人称单数: recites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comparison', '[kəm\'pærɪsn]', 'n.比较；比喻', '1. In comparison with other students, Mike is more diligent. 和其他学生相比，麦克更加勤勉一些。 2. We can only tell good from bad by comparison. 我们可以通过比较来分辨好坏。 3. Reports of consecutive years should also be available for comparison. 网站应登载连续数年的报告,方便读者作比较。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pursuit', '[pər\'suːt]', 'n.追求；追赶；工作', '1. His life is spent in the pursuit of pleasure. 他一生都在寻欢作乐。 2. We work hard in pursuit of happy life. 我们为追求幸福生活而努力工作。 3. What\'s your favorite pursuit? 你的爱好是什么？ 4. He exercises everyday in pursuit of health. 他为了健康而每天锻炼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('housework', '[\'haʊswɜːrk]', 'n.家务劳动', '1. Housework is usually miscellaneous and toilsome. 家务劳动通常是繁杂的。 2. Her hands were roughened by housework. 她的手由于家务劳动而变得粗糙。', '名词: houseworker');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thirty', '[\'θɜːrti]', 'num.三十', '1. I\'ll be thirty next year. 明年我就满三十岁了。 2. I get up at six thirty every morning. 我每天早上六点半起床。 3. She dashed off two letters in thirty minutes. 她在30分钟内写好了两封信。 4. There are more than thirty footmen in this hotel. 这家旅馆里有三十多名仆役。', '名词复数: thirties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('worthy', '[\'wɜːrði]', 'adj.有价值的；可尊敬的；值得的；配得上的 n.知名人士；杰出人物', '1. This is a worthy English-Chinese dictionary. 这是一本有价值的英汉词典。 2. This book is worthy of reading. 这本书值得一读。 3. No man thinks more highly than I do of the patriotism, as well as abilities, of the very worthy gentlemen who have just addressed the house. 没有人比我对刚刚向议会全体代表发言的可尊敬的先生们的爱国精神和才干更钦佩了。 4. Mr. Foker himself is a worthy man, though not of high extraction or indeed much education. 福克先生本人也是值得尊敬的,尽管他出身不太高贵,受的教育确实也有限。 5. I want you to sell these two and find more worthy replacements. 我需要你卖这些二和发现更多杰出人物替换。', '副词: worthily 比较级: worthier 最高级: worthiest 名词: worthiness 名词复数: worthies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intrigue', '[ɪn\'triːɡ]', 'vt.欺骗；激起 ... 的兴趣 vi.密谋 n.阴谋；私通；复杂的事', '1. The shapes of clouds intrigue me. 云的形状激起我的兴趣。 2. She was intriguing with her sister against her mother. 她和妹妹串通捣鬼和母亲作对。 3. Some of the members had been intriguing to get the secretary dismissed. 有些人一直密谋想让老板把秘书解雇。 4. I\'ll never intrigue against my friends 我决不会对我的朋友耍阴谋，施诡计。 5. It is said that he is a master of intrigue. 据说他是搞阴谋诡计的老手。', '副词: intriguingly 名词: intriguer 过去式: intrigued 过去分词: intrigued 现在分词: intriguing 第三人称单数: intrigues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('primitive', '[\'prɪmətɪv]', 'adj.原始的；简陋的 n.文艺复兴前的艺术家；原始人', '1. Primitive peoples deified the sun. 原始部落将太阳奉为神。 2. The constitution of a primitive society is not necessarily simple. 原始社会的结构并不一定就是简单的。 3. They built a primitive shelter out of the tree trunks 他们用一些树干建造了一个简陋的棚子。 4. Primitive people often lived in caves. 原始人常常住在山洞里。', '副词: primitively 名词: primitiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cash', '[kæʃ]', 'n.现金 vt.付现款；兑现 adj.现金的', '1. He paid the cash into his bank account. 他把现金存入银行帐户。 2. I have no cash on me. Can I pay you later? 我没带现金,我能否以后付给你? 3. Sorry, you can\'t sign the bill here, cash only, please. 对不起,我们这里不可以签单,请付现款吧。 4. I want to cash the balance of a traveler\'s letter of credit. 我要把旅行信用证的结余兑现。 5. The merchant\'s cash sales each day were $300. 那店主一天有300美元的现金售货收入。', '形容词: cashless 名词复数: cash 过去式: cashed 过去分词: cashed 现在分词: cashing 第三人称单数: cashes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('silent', '[\'saɪlənt]', 'adj.安静的；不吵闹的；沉默的；无言的', '1. Would you be good enough to keep silent? 请你保持安静好吗？ 2. The old house was quite silent. 这所旧房子非常寂静。 3. We sailed into a beautiful and silent bay. 我们驶进一个美丽而安静的海湾。 4. She was a silent girl, cool and remote. 她是一个沉默寡言的女孩，对人冷漠而孤傲。', '副词: silently 名词: silentness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('myself', '[maɪ\'self]', 'pron.我自己', '1. I started to enjoy this kind of music myself. 我自己也喜欢上这类音乐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('click', '[klɪk]', 'n.咔嗒声；[计]点击 v.（使）发出咔嗒声；点击', '1. Marsha heard the lock click softly. 玛莎听到锁轻轻地发出咔嗒一声。 2. Click on their names to find out more about them. 点击它们的名称以获取更多信息。 3. You can click here to download the file now. 你可以点击这里立刻下载文件。 4. The door clicked shut. 门咔嗒一声关上了。', '名词: clicker 过去式: clicked 过去分词: clicked 现在分词: clicking 第三人称单数: clicks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('canteen', '[kæn\'tiːn]', 'n.食堂；水壶', '1. He always bring a canteen with him on a hike. 他作徒步旅行时总是带着水壶。 2. This is a much frequented canteen. 这是一家就餐人数很多的食堂。 3. He always bring a canteen with him on a hike. 他作徒步旅行时总是带着水壶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('workshop', '[\'wɜːrkʃɑːp]', 'n.工场；车间；研讨会；讲习班', '1. The workshop has shut down and the workers are unemployed. 工厂关闭后工人失业了。 2. Workshop conditions are often noisy and dirty. 工场的环境经常是既嘈杂又肮脏。 3. There are more than fifty workers in this workshop. 这个车间里有五十多个工人。 4. She was always the first to arrive at the workshop. 她总是第一个来到车间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('absurd', '[əb\'sɜːrd]', 'adj.荒唐的；可笑的；不合理的 n.荒唐', '1. He finally recovered from an absurd infatuation. 他终于从荒唐的迷恋中醒悟过来。 2. What an absurd suggestion! 多荒谬的建议啊！ 3. We have no intention of lying down under these absurd allegations. 对这些荒谬的指控我们是不甘受辱的。 4. It was absurd of you to suggest such a thing. 你居然建议这样的事，太可笑了。 5. The proposal borders on the absurd. 该提议近乎可笑。', '副词: absurdly 名词: absurdity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('synthetic', '[sɪn\'θetɪk]', 'adj.合成的；人造的；综合的；虚伪的 n.合成物；人工制品', '1. The basin is made of synthetic resin. 这个盆是用合成树脂做的。 2. Some of the new synthetic dress materials do not crush . 有些新型合成衣料不会起皱。 3. The clerk passed off a synthetic diamond to that unsuspecting customer. 这个店员用人造钻石冒充真货卖给了那个轻信的顾客。 4. Latin is a synthetic language, while English is analytic. 拉丁文是一种综合性语言,而英语是一种分析性语言。 5. Corticosteroids and their synthetic analogs are used to treat rheumatism and other inflammatory ailments. 皮质类固醇及其合成物可用来治疗风湿病和其它炎症。', '副词: synthetically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('concrete', '[\'kɑːŋkriːt]', 'adj.具体的；实质性的；混凝土的 n.水泥；混凝土；具体物 v.凝结；结合', '1. I can\'t tell you anything concrete. 这具体的我也说不上来。 2. He had nothing concrete to fasten it upon. 他抓不到什么具体的证据。 3. The statue rests on a bed of concrete. 这座雕像立在混凝土的基座上。 4. Between these are fixed precast concrete external cladding panels. 在它们之间填上预制混凝土的外层空心板。 5. Tom tumbled over and hit his head on the concrete. 汤姆摔倒，头撞到水泥地。 6. The government concreted the road over. 政府用混凝土铺路。', '副词: concretely 名词: concreteness 过去式: concreted 过去分词: concreted 现在分词: concreting 第三人称单数: concretes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strive', '[straɪv]', 'vi.奋斗；努力；力求；斗争', '1. He strove for recognition as an artist. 他为获得艺术家的声誉而奋斗。 2. We should all strive to reunify the motherland. 我们共同努力,实现祖国统一。 3. I strive automatically to bring the world into harmony with my own nature. 我机械地努力以使这世界跟自己的性情协调一致。 4. The scientists strive for a breakthrough in cancer research. 科学家们力争在癌症研究方面有个突破。', '副词: strivingly 名词: striver 过去式: strove 过去分词: striven/strived 现在分词: striving 第三人称单数: strives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stem', '[stem]', 'n.柄；茎；干；船首 vi.起源于 vt.抽去 ... 的梗；给 ... 装柄；逆 ... 而行；阻止，遏制', '1. Don\'t eat the stem of a mushroom. 不要吃蘑菇的梗。 2. This is a plant stem that has been pithed. 这是一根已经除去木髓的植物的茎。 3. Crime and punishment grow out of one stem. 罪与罚本是同茎生。 4. She bought some roses with long stems. 她买了一些枝干很长的玫瑰花。 5. Your errors stem all from your carelessness. 你犯的错误全都是由于你的粗心。 6. Our ship stemmed on against the current. 我们的船逆流而上。', '过去式: stemmed 过去分词: stemmed 现在分词: stemming 第三人称单数: stems');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('housewife', '[\'haʊswaɪf]', 'n.家庭主妇 n.针线盒', '1. She typifies the bored housewife. 她是那种百无聊赖的家庭主妇的典型。 2. Many women chose to be a housewife after marriage. 许多妇女选择了在婚后当家庭主妇。', '名词复数: housewives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('distill', '[dɪs\'tɪl]', 'v.蒸馏；滴下；吸取；提炼', '1. When carvone begins to distill, the condensation can be seen inside the thermometer adapter, thus the progress of carvone distillation can be readily monitored. 当香芹酮开始蒸馏时，在温度计转接器内可看到有冷凝，因此能够容易地监察香芹酮的蒸馏过程。 2. You had to somehow distill those feelings. 你必须试图一滴一滴提炼出这些感情。 3. We were asked to distill the crucial points of the book. 要求我们从本书中提炼出关键点。', '形容词: distillable');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rural', '[\'rʊrəl]', 'adj.农村的，乡村的，田园的', '1. The disease occurs most frequently in rural areas. 那疾病多见於农村地区。 2. Rural areas have been worst hit by the strike. 受罢工影响最严重的是乡村地区。 3. The rural scenery was so beautiful that he decided to stay one more week. 乡村风光太美了，以致于他决定再多呆一星期。 4. Nine tenths of the population in rural areas live from hand to mouth. 农村地区90%25的人仅够糊口。', '副词: rurally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hatch', '[hætʃ]', 'n.孵化；舱口，舱口盖 v.孵；孵出；策划', '1. The hatch date for tit eggs appears to be determined about a month earlier, when the eggs are laid. 白颊山雀孵化的时间，似乎在孵化前一个月，也就是下蛋时便已决定。 2. Both men quickly disappeared down the hatch. 两个人很快从舱口下去不见了。 3. We heard the noise of a hatch being closed. 我们听到关舱口的声音。 4. An incubator is used to hatch chicken. 孵卵器用来孵小鸡。', '名词: hatcher 过去式: hatched 过去分词: hatched 现在分词: hatching 第三人称单数: hatches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pattern', '[\'pætərn]', 'n.模式；图案；典范；式样 v.以图案装饰；仿造；模仿', '1. The two buildings are modeled after the same pattern. 这两座建筑是按照同一模式建造的。 2. Training and education follow different patterns in different regions. 培训和教育在不同的地区遵循不同的模式。 3. This cloth has a pattern of blue and white squares. 这种布有蓝白格子的图案。 4. Threads of different colors and textures were woven into an intricate pattern. 各种花色和质地的线织成了一幅复杂的图案。 5. I like the carpets patterned with peonies. 我喜欢印有牡丹花图案的地毯。', '过去式: patterned 过去分词: patterned 现在分词: patterning 第三人称单数: patterns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('principle', '[\'prɪnsəpl]', 'n.原理；原则；主义；信念', '1. A bicycle and a motorcycle are built on the same principle. 自行车和摩托车是根据同样的原理制造的。 2. Archimedes ,a great physicist ,discovered the principle of floating bodies . 阿基米德，一位伟大的物理学家，发现了浮体原理。 3. We adhere to the principle that everyone should be treated fairly. 我们坚持人人都应该被平等对待这一原则。 4. It is easier to fight for one\'s principle than to live up to them. 为自己的主义斗争，要比他们施诸实践更容易。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kin', '[kɪn]', 'n.家族；亲属 adj.亲属关系的；同类的 suf.(接名词后)小的', '1. The conversion will be a tendency for kin enterprise in China. 中国的家族企业进行转型将成为一种趋势。 2. However, the Mesozoic is best known as the age of reptiles, when dinosaurs and their kin dominated the continents. 但中生代还是以爬行动物时代而著名，在这个时期，恐龙以及它们的家族统治了整个大陆。 3. All our kin came to the family reunion. 我们的亲属全都参加了这次家庭团聚会。 4. Her next of kin have been informed. 已通知她最近的亲属了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('advance', '[əd\'væns]', 'n.前进；进展；预付金 v.前进；预付；增长；推进 adj.预先的；提前的', '1. Advance in the jungle was very slow. 在丛林中行进很慢。 2. There have been great progresses in medicine in the past decade. 在过去十年里,医学取得了巨大的进步。 3. She asked for an advance on her salary. 她请求预支薪水。 4. The officer directed them to advance. 指挥官命令他们前进。 5. There was no advance warning before the earthquake hit. 地震之前没有任何预兆。', '名词: advancer 过去式: advanced 过去分词: advanced 现在分词: advancing 第三人称单数: advances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lease', '[liːs]', 'n.租约；租契；租期 vt.出租；租得', '1. Our present lease on the flat expires next month. 我们这套公寓的租约下月到期。 2. An astute tenant always reads the small print in a lease. 精明的租户对租契上的每个细小之处都要讲究。 3. Does your current lease provide for showings prior to the tenant vacating the property? 您当前的租契是否规定了在房客搬出房间之前可以提前展售？ 4. The lease of my house has only a year to run . 我的房子的租约期限只有1年了。 5. This company leases out property. 这个公司出租房地产。', '形容词: leasable 名词: leaser 过去式: leased 过去分词: leased 现在分词: leasing 第三人称单数: leases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('under', '[\'ʌndər]', 'prep.低于；在 ... 下；在 ... 内；在 ... 控制下 adv.在昏迷中；在 ... 下 adj.下面的；从属的；少于的', '1. The watch cannot be sold for under 100 yuan. 这块表低于100元不卖。 2. The total is under what was expected. 总数低于预计数。 3. No one under the rank of captain may enter the room. 级别低于上尉者禁止入内。 4. Many children under five go to nursery school. 5岁以下的许多儿童都上幼儿园。 5. She felt herself going under. 她感到渐渐失去了知觉。 6. Can you see the under layer? 你能看到下面那层吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('once', '[wʌns]', 'adv.一次；曾经 conj.一旦 n.一次 adj.曾经的', '1. Once or twice she looked over her shoulder at me. 有一两次她回头看看我。 2. She had not once spoken to him all the evening. 整整一晚上,她都没有跟他讲过一次话。 3. I see them about once a fortnight. 我大约两星期见他们一次。 4. Once we lived in London. 我们曾经住在伦敦。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('banner', '[\'bænər]', 'n.横幅；旗帜；大标题 adj.杰出的；特别好的 vt.用横幅装饰；以大标题报道', '1. Can you read that banner from this distance? 从这里你能看清那个横幅标语吗? 2. Do not use excessive banner advertisements. 不要使用过多的横幅广告。 3. The banner lent color to the streets. 旗帜给街道增添了色彩。 4. The patriots fought under the banner of freedom. 爱国者在自由的旗帜下战斗。 5. This year is a banner year for crops. 今年是个丰年。 6. The report was bannered by the People\'s Daily. 《人民日报》用横贯全页的大标题形式进行了报道。', '过去式: bannered 过去分词: bannered 现在分词: bannering 第三人称单数: banners');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ham', '[hæm]', 'n.火腿；（动物）后腿 v.表演过火；演技夸张', '1. This ham has too much fat on it. 这火腿肥肉太多。 2. He tucked into the ham hungrily. 他狼吞虎咽地大吃火腿。 3. He made a ham sandwich. 他做了一个火腿三明治。 4. The actor is really ham it up to amuse the audience. 这些演员为博观众一笑,表演得实在太过火了。', '过去式: hammed 过去分词: hammed 现在分词: hamming 第三人称单数: hams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('senior', '[\'siːniər]', 'adj.地位较高的；高级的；年长的；资深的 n.上司；年长者；长辈；大四学生', '1. He is senior to me, though he is younger. 他地位比我高，虽然他比我年轻。 2. She was unfit for such a senior position. 她不能胜任这样的高级职位。 3. Lying north of the church is a girls\' senior high school. 位于这座教堂以北的是一所女子高中。 4. Although he is senior to his wife, he is inferior to her in salary. 虽然她年长于他的妻子,但他妻子的收入比他高。 5. The three vice-ministers are my seniors. 三位副部长都是我的上司。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crawl', '[krɔːl]', 'v.爬行；卑躬屈膝；自由式游泳 n.爬行；匍匐而行；[体]自由式游泳', '1. The baby is just learning to crawl. 那个婴儿正在学习爬行。 2. Soldiers quietly crawl to advance to enemy. 士兵们悄悄地向敌人匍匐前进。 3. You must not crawl into the favor of your superiors. 你不应卑躬屈膝地讨好你的上司。 4. I hate people who creep and crawl to others. 我讨厌那些阿谀奉承的人。 5. The crawl of snake is terrifying. 蛇爬行起来真可怕。', '副词: crawlingly 过去式: crawled 过去分词: crawled 现在分词: crawling 第三人称单数: crawls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('graceful', '[\'ɡreɪsfl]', 'adj.优雅的；得体的', '1. Her every movement is very graceful. 她的一举一动都很优美。 2. We admired the graceful poise of the dancer. 我们很欣赏那位舞蹈演员的优美舞姿。 3. His refusal was worded in such a graceful way that we could not be offended. 他的拒绝是那样委婉得体，所以我们并未感到不快。 4. He made a graceful speech accepting the award. 他作了一个得体的获奖演说。', '副词: gracefully 名词: gracefulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coarse', '[kɔːrs]', 'adj.粗糙的；粗俗的；非精制的', '1. The medicine powder is too coarse, keep grinding it. 药面太粗了，再磨细点。 2. His coarse manners shocked everyone. 他的粗鲁的举止使每个人震惊。', '副词: coarsely 比较级: coarser 最高级: coarsest 名词: coarseness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disguise', '[dɪs\'ɡaɪz]', 'vt.掩饰；假装；假扮 n.伪装；伪装物', '1. She could not disguise her amusement at his mistake. 她对他的错误忍俊不禁。 2. It proved difficult to disguise his anxiety. 他的焦虑难以掩饰。 3. She disguised herself as a man, but she couldn\'t disguise her voice. 她把自己乔装成一个男子，但她改变不了自己的声音。 4. He plans to disguise himself as a policeman. 他打算把自己假扮成一个警察。 5. The supposed beggar was really a police officer in disguise. 那个众人眼中的乞丐，其实是化了装的警察。', '副词: disguisedly 名词: disguisement 过去式: disguised 过去分词: disguised 现在分词: disguising 第三人称单数: disguises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('corridor', '[\'kɔːrɪdɔːr]', 'n.走廊', '1. She finally nailed me in the corridor. 她最後在走廊里把我抓住了。 2. The thief crept along the corridor. 那贼偷偷地在走廊上潜行。 3. I\'m a bit suspicious about the package that\'s been left in the corridor. 我对一直放在走廊里的那个包裹有些怀疑。 4. My room is at the end of the corridor. 我的房间在走廊的尽头。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commercial', '[kə\'mɜːrʃl]', 'adj.商业的 n.商业广告', '1. Do you fancy having a go at doing a commercial feature film? 对制作商业的影片有没有兴趣? 2. The downtown area is zoned for commercial use. 市中心被划出供商业用。 3. They were much more realistic about its long term commercial prospects. 他们对它的长远商业前景更为现实。 4. The Dole commercial is the first time Pfizer has promoted Viagra through television. 多尔的广告是辉瑞首次通过电视推销伟哥。', '副词: commercially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scrape', '[skreɪp]', 'v.刮掉；擦掉 n.擦伤；擦掉；刮擦声；<口>窘境', '1. I must have scraped some of the paint off when I was parking the car. 我准是停放汽车的时候刮掉了一些油漆。 2. He bent over to scrape some dirt off his shoes. 他弯腰刮掉鞋子上的尘土。 3. Scrape your shoes on the door mat before you come in. 进屋前先在门口擦鞋垫上擦一擦鞋子。 4. He suffered a few cuts and scrapes. 他割破和擦伤了几个地方。', '过去式: scraped 过去分词: scraped 现在分词: scraping 第三人称单数: scrapes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('market', '[\'mɑːrkɪt]', 'n.市场；集市 v.销售；推销；买卖', '1. The market is rather depressed at the moment. 目前的市场相当萧条。 2. The sales manager wants to open up new markets in the Far East. 销售经理想在远东开辟新市场。 3. I bought a coconut in the market. 我在集市上买了一个椰子。 4. The inventor is trying to market his new product. 发明者正想销售他的新产品。', '过去式: marketed 过去分词: marketed 现在分词: marketing 第三人称单数: markets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('test', '[test]', 'n.考验；试验；测试 vt.试验；测试；接受测验', '1. We achieved within seven months an agreement that has stood the test of time. 我们在七个月内完成一项协议,而且经受住了时间的考验。 2. Our test flight was to discover the bugs in the new plane. 试验飞行是为了发现新飞机有何毛病。 3. Tomorrow we\'ll have a history test. 明天我们将进行历史测验。 4. By doing so, you can test the strength of steel. 这样做,你可以试验一下钢的强度。', '形容词: testable 名词: testability 过去式: tested 过去分词: tested 现在分词: testing 第三人称单数: tests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invaluable', '[ɪn\'væljuəbl]', 'adj.无价的；非常珍贵的', '1. But the experience they will gain is invaluable. 但他们从此获得的经验是无价的。 2. His experience proved an invaluable help. 他的经验被证明是无价之宝。 3. The painting is an invaluable treasure. 这幅画是无价之宝。 4. This set of ancient china is invaluable. 这套古瓷器非常珍贵。', '副词: invaluably 名词: invaluableness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Wednesday', '[\'wenzdeɪ]', 'n.星期三', '1. What day is today? It\'s Wednesday. 今天是星期几？今天是星期三。 2. I have an appointment on Wednesday. 我星期三有个约会。 3. If today is Wednesday, the day after tomorrow will be Friday. 今天要是星期三,后天就是星期五。 4. The steamers for Shanghai leave on Wednesday. 开往上海的轮船星期三启程。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lantern', '[\'læntərn]', 'n.灯笼；[建]天窗；屋顶气窗', '1. I\'m making a paper lantern for my nephew. 我做了个纸灯笼给我的外甥。 2. A little lantern blinked in the darkness. 一盏小灯笼在黑暗中微微闪光。 3. The Chinese palace lanterns are famous for their delicacy. 中国的宫灯以精巧闻名。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('three', '[θriː]', 'num.三 n.三；三个 adj.三个的', '1. He is only a child of three. 他只是一个三岁的孩子。 2. Three of the chickens hatched today. 今天有三只小鸡出壳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('republican', '[rɪ\'pʌblɪkən]', 'n.拥护共和政体的人 adj.共和政体的 Republican: 共和党人. Republican: 共和党的.', '1. In much the same tone of voice, a voter in Michigan said she like President Reagan and thought \"I better not rock the boat, so I\'ll go with a Republican again this time.\" 密歇根一位选民以几乎同样的语调说，她喜欢里根总统，她心想，“我别无事生非，所以我这次还是追随共和党。” 2. German-born American editorial cartoonist whose caricatures in Harper\'s Weekly contributed to the downfall of the Tweed Ring in New York City. He also established the donkey and the elephant as symbols of the Democratic and Republican parties. 纳斯特，托马斯1840－1902德裔美国社论卡通画家，他刊登在《哈泼周刊》上的作品对特威德集团在纽约市的垮台很有影响。他还曾创作象征共和党的大象和民主党的毛驴形象 3. Charles is a dyed-in-the-wool Republican. 查尔斯是个彻头彻尾的共和党人。 4. The United States shall guarantee to every state in this union a republican form of government. 美利坚合众国保证合众国各州实行共和政体。', '名词: republicanism');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('worship', '[\'wɜːrʃɪp]', 'n.崇拜；爱慕；做礼拜 vi.做礼拜 vt.崇拜；爱慕', '1. He deserves all the praise and worship. 他值得我们一切的赞美和崇拜。 2. She scorn the girls who worship football stars. 她看不起那些崇拜足球明星的女孩子。 3. She was blind to the silent worship in his eyes. 她没有发觉他眼里流露出的无声的敬慕之情。 4. This is the church where we used to worship. 这就是那座我们过去常做礼拜的教堂。 5. This is the church where we used to worship. 这就是那座我们过去常做礼拜的教堂。 6. The boy worshipped his father. 这小孩崇拜他的父亲。', '名词: worshiper 过去式: worshiped/worshipped 过去分词: worshiped/worshipped 现在分词: worshiping/worshipping 第三人称单数: worships/worships');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comfort', '[\'kʌmfərt]', 'n.舒适；安逸；安慰；慰藉 vt.安慰；使舒适', '1. The dress is carefully styled for maximum comfort. 这服装精心设计，力求达到最大限度的舒适。 2. First, you need to get out of your comfort zone. 首先,你要离开你的习惯,离开你的舒适地带。 3. Humanization design is to upgrade the comfort of operation. 人性化设计,更提升了操作舒适性。 4. They are now living in relative comfort. 他们现在过着比较安逸的生活。 5. I tried to comfort him after he was defeated by his opponent. 他被对手击败后，我尽力安慰他。', '副词: comfortingly 过去式: comforted 过去分词: comforted 现在分词: comforting 第三人称单数: comforts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shy', '[ʃaɪ]', 'adj.腼腆的；胆怯的；害羞的', '1. He was too shy to talk to anyone at the party. 在晚会上他很腼腆，没有和任何人讲话。 2. He only saw her sweet, shy face. 他只注意到她的甜甜的、腼腆的脸。 3. We must not fight shy of hard work. 我们不应回避艰苦的工作。 4. The shy girl was afraid to contradict. 这个害羞的女孩不敢提出反驳意见。', '副词: shyly 比较级: shier/shyer 最高级: shiest/shyest 名词: shyer 名词复数: shies 过去式: shied 过去分词: shied 现在分词: shying 第三人称单数: shies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('altitude', '[\'æltɪtuːd]', 'n.高度；海拔；高地', '1. We are flying at an altitude of 20000 feet. 我们的飞行高度是20000英尺。 2. Air pressure decreases with altitude. 气压随海拔高度的增加而下降。 3. At this altitude there is no screening from the sun\'s rays. 在这种海拔高度，没有遮阳处。 4. At this altitude you often get strong winds. 在这一纬度地区，经常有大风。', '形容词: altitudinal');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bully', '[\'bʊli]', 'n.欺凌弱小者；开球 vt.恐吓；威胁；欺负', '1. The little girl stood up to a bully. 小女孩勇敢地对付暴徒。 2. The bully whacked my brother with a stick. 那恶棍用棒头狠揍我兄弟。 3. Leave that little girl alone, you big bully! 离那小姑娘远点儿, 你这个大坏蛋! 4. You are not discreet; you mustn\'t bully me. 你真不客气，你休想恐吓我。', '名词复数: bullies 过去式: bullied 过去分词: bullied 现在分词: bullying 第三人称单数: bullies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reach', '[riːtʃ]', 'v.到达；伸出；达成；取得联系；延伸；（伸手）去够 n.范围；影响力；河段；等级', '1. We had twenty miles to cover to reach the nearest railway station. 我们得走20英里的路才能到达最近的火车站。 2. He reached into his pocket to get his car keys. 他把手伸进口袋里拿车钥匙。 3. Hopefully, they will reach an agreement after the talk. 会谈之后,他们有望达成协议。 4. We tried to reach them by cable. 我们试着用电报跟他们联络。 5. The plates on the upper shelf are beyond my reach. 上层架子上的盘子我伸手拿不到。', '形容词: reachable 名词: reacher 过去式: reached 过去分词: reached 现在分词: reaching 第三人称单数: reaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cold', '[koʊld]', 'adj.冷的；寒冷的；冷酷的；冷淡的；冷静的 n.寒冷；感冒；伤风 adv.完全地；彻底地', '1. We lunched out on cold meat and salad. 我们午饭在外面吃的是凉肉和色拉。 2. It was bitterly cold that night. 那个夜晚,天气十分寒冷。 3. His cold manner holds people off. 他的冷淡态度使人们不敢接近他。 4. Our enthusiasm for the plan faded in the cold light of day and we realized how impractical it really was. 经过客观冷静的分析，我们对这个计划的热情消失了，因为我们认识到它实在不实际了。 5. The dampness is unpleasant,not to mention the cold. 潮湿就令人不快,更不必说寒冷了。 6. John knew the business cold. 约翰对此事了如指掌。', '副词: coldly 比较级: colder 最高级: coldest 名词: coldness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('postpone', '[poʊ\'spoʊn]', 'vt.延期；推迟', '1. The weather being bad, we had to postpone our trip. 因为天气不好,我们不得不延期出行。 2. She did not postpone her departure. 她不再延迟她的行期。 3. Can we postpone the meeting till tomorrow? 我们可以把会议延到明天吗? 4. The commander decided to postpone the big push until the spring. 指挥官决定把大规模的进攻推迟到春天进行。', '形容词: postponable 名词: postponement 过去式: postponed 过去分词: postponed 现在分词: postponing 第三人称单数: postpones');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shear', '[ʃɪr]', 'n.修剪；剪下的东西；大剪刀 v.剪掉；剪；剥夺', '1. With a few quick snips of the shear, he pruned the bush. 他用大剪刀几下子就把灌木给修剪好了。 2. All her curls have been shorn off. 她的一头卷发被剪得精光。 3. I start shearing the sheep at the beginning of July. 我一般在7月初开始剪羊毛。', '名词: shearer 过去式: sheared 过去分词: sheared/shorn 现在分词: shearing 第三人称单数: shears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('liquor', '[\'lɪkər]', 'n.酒；烈性酒；液剂', '1. Many airports sell duty-free liquor. 很多机场出售免税酒。 2. He appears to have drunk a lot of liquor. 他似乎喝得醉醺醺的。 3. Drinking hard liquor too much is harmful to health. 喝太多的烈性酒对身体有害。 4. Stay off the hard liquor until your stomach feels better. 等你的胃舒服了再喝烈性酒。', '过去式: liquored 过去分词: liquored 现在分词: liquoring 第三人称单数: liquors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tow', '[toʊ]', 'v.拖；拉；牵引 n.拖；拽；拖绳', '1. We have to tow that car to the nearest garage. 我们不得不把汽车拖到最近的修车厂。 2. The ship needed two tugs to tow it into port. 这艘船需用两艘拖船把它拖进港。 3. The broken-down car was taken in tow by a lorry. 一辆卡车拉着一辆坏了的汽车。 4. When she sits at the beach, Greenpeace tries to tow her back into the ocean. 你妈妈胖到她座在沙滩上时，绿色和平组织会尝试著把她拉回大海里。 5. My car\'s broken down; will you give me a tow? 我的车抛锚了，能用你的车给我拖一拖吗？', '形容词: towable 名词: tower 过去式: towed 过去分词: towed 现在分词: towing 第三人称单数: tows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ballot', '[\'bælət]', 'n.投票；投票用纸 vi.投票', '1. We should put it to a ballot. 我们应该对此进行无记名投票。 2. He was elected by ballot. 他是由无记名投票选举的。 3. The new act stipulates that election to union office shall be by secret ballot of members. 新法规定工会职位的选举将由会员秘密投票方式进行。 4. Each voter receives a unique ballot code. 每一个投票人会收到一个独一的选票号码。 5. They decided to ballot for competing lanes. 他们决定抽签选择比赛跑道。', '名词: balloter 过去式: balloted 过去分词: balloted 现在分词: balloting 第三人称单数: ballots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('timely', '[\'taɪmli]', 'adj.及时的；适时的 adv.及时的', '1. What we expected is nothing less than a timely payment. 及时付款正是我们所盼望的。 2. Had it not been for your timely help, our company would have been on the verge of bankruptcy. 若非你及时伸出援助之手,本公司将会濒临破产。 3. His wife was so poignant and timely. 他的妻子是这样有分寸和适时宜。 4. I think timely rain is good for the crops. 我认为适时地下雨对庄稼生长有好处。 5. I really appreciate your timely help. 真的感谢你及时的帮忙。', '比较级: timelier 最高级: timeliest 名词: timeliness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assemble', '[ə\'sembl]', 'v.集合；收集；装配', '1. The students assembled in the school garden. 学生们在校园集合。 2. If the fire-alarm goes, staff should assemble outside the building. 火警警报响时全体人员应到楼外集合。 3. Assemble your papers and put them in the file . 把你们的论文收集起来归档。 4. The processing and assemble business is a component part of our foreign trade. 加工和装配贸易是我国对外贸易的一个组成部分。', '过去式: assembled 过去分词: assembled 现在分词: assembling 第三人称单数: assembles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('constituent', '[kən\'stʃuənt]', 'n.成分；选民；构成物 adj.构成的；组织的；立宪的', '1. Do you know the constituents of the mixture? 你知道这种混合物的成分吗？ 2. Punctuality is an important constituent of good character. 准时是优良品格的一个重要成分。 3. Last week, a constituent contacted me and asked me to help him construe an article contained within the constitution. 上星期，一位选民跟我联系，让我帮他解释一下宪法中包含的某则条款。 4. The chemical dissolves into its constituent parts when heated. 该化学药剂加热时会分解成其组成的分子。', '副词: constituently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('complement', '[\'kɑːmplɪment]', 'vt.相辅相成 n.补足物；补语；余角', '1. This wine complements the food perfectly. 用这种酒配这种菜肴最妙不过了。 2. His business skill complements her flair for design. 他的经营技巧和她的设计才能相辅相成。 3. A wine is a complement to a good meal. 美食加美酒才算完备。 4. In the sentence \'I\'m angry\', \'angry\' is the complement. 在I\'m angry一句中,angry是补语。', '过去式: complemented 过去分词: complemented 现在分词: complementing 第三人称单数: complements');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jargon', '[\'dʒɑːrɡən]', 'n.行话 vi.说行话', '1. Expert often confuse laymen with their jargon. 专家们常常用行话把外行弄得稀里糊涂。 2. The jargon in his talk was opaque to me. 他谈话中使用的行话对我是一团迷雾。 3. Scientists are notoriously fond of jargon. 科学家爱用行话到了声名狼藉的地步。', '形容词: jargonistic 名词: jargonist 过去式: jargoned 过去分词: jargoned 现在分词: jargoning 第三人称单数: jargons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cue', '[kjuː]', 'n.暗示；提示；信号；（台球的）球杆 vt.给 ... 提示；把 ... 插入演出', '1. When I nod my head, that\'s your cue to interrupt the meeting. 我一点头，就是暗示你把会议中断。 2. The actor picked up his cue with effect. 演员对他所得到的提示迅速地作出了反应，效果良好。 3. The horses reacted as if on cue. 马像得了信号一样地起了反应。 4. Can you cue me when you want me to begin speaking? 你要我开始讲话时能给我暗示一下吗?', '过去式: cued 过去分词: cued 现在分词: cuing 第三人称单数: cues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('madame', '[\'mædəm]', 'n.夫人', '1. Madame Curie won two Nobel Prizes. 居里夫人两次获得了诺贝尔奖。 2. Madame believes in rigid discipline. 夫人的纪律非常严格。 3. Madam is not receiving callers today . 夫人今天不接见来客。', '名词复数: Mesdames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('context', '[\'kɒntekst]', 'n.上下文；环境；背景', '1. It is usually easier to pick out the meaning of a phrase in a given context. 在特定的上下文中理解一个短语的含意往往要更容易些。 2. In the context of the present economic crisis it seems unwise to lower taxes. 鉴於当前的经济危机，降低税率似乎不妥。 3. This speech needs to be set in the context of Britain in the 1960s. 这篇演说需要放到20世纪60年代的英国这一背景之下来看待。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('notebook', '[\'noʊtbʊk]', 'n.笔记本；笔记本电脑', '1. I record all my thoughts in a notebook. 我在笔记本上记下我所有的想法。 2. She filled her notebook with sketches. 她在笔记本上画满素描。 3. The ultimate big prize will be notebook one! 终极大奖将是笔记本电脑一台！ 4. Use this pc, and notebook together. 这台笔记本电脑和台式电脑你花搭着用吧！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('servant', '[\'sɜːrvənt]', 'n.仆人', '1. Satan is still a servant of God. 撒旦仍是上帝的奴仆。 2. The servant enjoyed his master\'s confidence. 这仆人深得主人的信赖。 3. He is a humble and submissive servant. 他是个恭顺的仆人。 4. A politician should be a servant of the people. 政治家应是人民的公仆。', '名词复数: servants');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pronounce', '[prə\'naʊns]', 'vt.发音；宣告；宣判；断言 vi.发音；发表意见', '1. I don\'t know how to pronounce this word. 我不知道这个单词怎么发音。 2. People pronounce the word differently in this part of the country. 在国内这一地区，这个单词的发音不同。 3. The doctors pronounced that he was no longer in danger. 医生宣称他已脱离危险。 4. The court pronounced her innocent of all charges. 法庭宣判所有的对她指控撤销。 5. Healthy teeth can help us pronounce accurately. 健康的牙齿可以帮助我们准确发音。', '形容词: pronounceable 名词: pronunciation 过去式: pronounced 过去分词: pronounced 现在分词: pronouncing 第三人称单数: pronounces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('six', '[sɪks]', 'num.六', '1. It is about six o\'clock now. 现在是六点钟左右。 2. The heifer is only six months old. 这只小母牛只有六个月大。 3. The murder trial lasted six weeks. 法庭对这一谋杀案的审理为时六周。 4. The tree is said to be six hundred years old. 这树约莫已有600年树龄了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('canoe', '[kə\'nuː]', 'n.独木舟 v.乘独木舟；用独木舟运', '1. We crossed the lake in a canoe. 我们乘独木舟过河。 2. If you stand up you\'ll overbalance the canoe. 要是站起来，能把独木舟弄翻。 3. The canoe was sucked down into the whirlpool. 划艇被卷进了旋涡。 4. They were canoeing in the lake. 他们在湖中划独木舟。', '名词: canoeist 过去式: canoed 过去分词: canoed 现在分词: canoeing 第三人称单数: canoes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shorthand', '[\'ʃɔːrthænd]', 'n.速记；缩写', '1. She thought of brushing up her shorthand. 她想到要复习一下过去学过的速记术。 2. He took down the minute in shorthand. 他将会议记录速记下来。 3. Others see it as no more menacing than shorthand for telegrams or typing. 其他人则认为其威胁性并不高于电报或速记里的缩写带来的影响。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cat', '[kæt]', 'n.猫；猫科动物；狠毒的女人；吊锚机；独桅船；九尾鞭 v.起锚；寻找性伴侣 abbr.目录（=catalog）', '1. A cat mews. 猫喵喵叫。 2. The cat lapped up the milk. 猫舔食牛奶。 3. The cat is playing with a live mouse. 猫在戏弄那只活老鼠。 4. The tiger is a representative of the cat family. 老虎是猫科动物的典型。', '过去式: catted 过去分词: catted 现在分词: catting 第三人称单数: cats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relate', '[rɪ\'leɪt]', 'v.叙述；使有联系；有关联；涉及；符合；发生共鸣', '1. To what events did your remarks relate? 你的话指的是什么事? 2. It is difficult to relate cause and effect in this case. 这个案件中的动机与结果很难联系起来。 3. These two events were related to each other. 这两个事件相互有联系。 4. In what way does it relate to your current career? 这跟您目前的职业有何关联呢?。', '形容词: relatable 名词: relater 过去式: related 过去分词: related 现在分词: relating 第三人称单数: relates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('module', '[\'mɑːdʒul]', 'n.组件；单元；模块；模数；(航天器的)舱；（组成一门课程的）独立单元', '1. My desk is my command module. 我的书桌就是我的主要工作场所。 2. Have an overall pass for each module of the programme. 通过每单元之综合评核。 3. A module is a compilation unit or a development unit. 模块是编译单元或开发单元。 4. You will be able to see the contents of that module. 您将能够看到该模块的内容。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discharge', '[dɪs\'tʃɑːrdʒ]', 'v.排出；释放；解雇；放电；解除；清偿债务 n.卸货；释放；发射；放电；准许离开；排出物', '1. The Nile discharge itself into the Mediterranean. 尼罗河水注入地中海。 2. The water pipe doesn\'t discharge freely. 水管排水不畅。 3. The judge discharged the prisoner. 法官把囚犯释放了。 4. I am going to discharge our chauffeur. 我要解雇我们的司机。 5. How long will the discharge of the cargo take? 卸货需要多久？', '形容词: dischargeable 名词: dischargee 过去式: discharged 过去分词: discharged 现在分词: discharging 第三人称单数: discharges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jug', '[dʒʌɡ]', 'n.水壶；罐；<俚>监牢 vt.罐焖；<俚>把……关进监狱', '1. She filled the jug with fresh water. 她将水壶注满了清水。 2. I managed to grab hold of the jug before it fell. 我设法抓住了那个罐子才未跌落。 3. When I tried to lift the jug, the handle came off. 我刚一提这个罐,把儿就掉了。 4. She poured some water into the earthenware jug. 她向那个陶罐里倒了些水。 5. He invited me to eat some jugged hare with him together. 他邀请我和他一块吃些罐焖野兔。', '过去式: jugged 过去分词: jugged 现在分词: jugging 第三人称单数: jugs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pit', '[pɪt]', 'n.坑；矿井；陷阱；凹痕；(剧院的)正厅后排；（枣）核 vt.使凹陷；使竞争 vi.凹陷', '1. The children were playing in the sand pit. 孩子们在沙坑中玩耍。 2. They dug a pit to bury the rubbish. 他们挖了一个坑把垃圾埋掉。 3. I\'ve got quite used to working in the pit. 在矿井工作我已经很习惯了。 4. When you fall into a pit, you either die or get out. 当你落入陷阱中,不是设法逃出,就是死路一条。 5. The ground was pitted by the heavy rain. 大雨使场地变得坑坑洼洼。', '过去式: pitted 过去分词: pitted 现在分词: pitting 第三人称单数: pits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('restraint', '[rɪ\'streɪnt]', 'n.克制；抑制；束缚', '1. The police appealed to the crowd for restraint. 警方呼吁群众保持克制。 2. Nobody could count on his restraint or rationality. 谁也不能指望他会克制或讲道理的态度。 3. There is still need for profit restraint. 现在仍有必要限制利润。 4. His rage was beyond restraint. 他怒不可遏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sightseeing', '[\'saɪtsiːɪŋ]', 'n.【U】观光；游览', '1. I spent most of my time in sightseeing. 我大部分时间都用在观光游览上了。 2. We spent the remainder of the day sightseeing. 这天剩下的时间我们到各处观光。 3. They embarked on an orgy of sightseeing. 他们开始尽情地观光游览。 4. Good morning, Mr.Smith. Sightseeing is our agenda today. 早上好，史密斯先生。我们今天的日程安排是游览。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ticket', '[\'tɪkɪt]', 'n.票；券；标签；罚单；候选人名单 vt.加标签于；售票；开罚单；检票，查验票证', '1. Have you got your train ticket? 你拿到火车票了吗？ 2. No one is allowed to get his ticket out of turn. 任何人都不准不按次序买票。 3. The money is raised by the sale of raffle ticket. 这笔款是通过出售购物彩券筹集的。 4. The ticket tells you the price of this dress. 标签告诉你这件衣服的价钱。 5. All articles in the store are ticketed with the price. 店里的所有物品都有标签标明价格。', '过去式: ticketed 过去分词: ticketed 现在分词: ticketing 第三人称单数: tickets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('genuine', '[\'dʒenjuɪn]', 'adj.真诚的；真正的；真实的；地道的', '1. He has a genuine desire to help us. 他真心诚意地愿意帮助我们。 2. A genuine friend will not desert you in time of adversity. 真正的朋友不会在患难时弃你而去。 3. It appears to be genuine, but I have my suspicions (about it). 这看来好像是真的，不过我(对此)有怀疑。 4. Viewed from the outside, the company seemed genuine. 从外表上看，这家公司倒像是真的。', '副词: genuinely 名词: genuineness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('web', '[web]', 'n.网；网络；网状物；腹板 vi.结网 vt.结网于；使陷入罗网', '1. A spider weaves a web to catch prey. 蜘蛛为捕猎昆虫而织网。 2. The tiger was enmeshed in the web laid by hunter. 老虎缠在猎人布下的网里。 3. Do you think art and design are melding on the web? 你认为在网络上艺术和设计是相结合的吗？ 4. He breathlessly watched the spider attempt to spin its web for the third time. 他凝神屏息地观看那蜘蛛试图第三次结网。 5. Do you think that the spider can web anything? 你觉得这蜘蛛能用网捕住什么吗?', '过去式: webbed 过去分词: webbed 现在分词: webbing 第三人称单数: webs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('young', '[jʌŋ]', 'adj.年轻的；初期的；没有经验的 n.青年人；幼崽', '1. The young look is in fashion this year. 今年时兴扮年轻人的样子。 2. Those clothes she\'s wearing are much too young for her. 她穿的那些衣服显得太年轻了。 3. The evening is still young. 晚间刚开始不久。 4. He was young in this kind of work. 他对这种工作经验不多。 5. The young in our society need care and protection. 我们社会的年轻人需要关怀和照顾。', '比较级: younger 最高级: youngest 名词: youngness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('field', '[fiːld]', 'n.田地；领域；运动场；场地；田野；JAVA中的范畴 vt.接球；派……上场；顺利处理 vi.担任外场员 adj.田间的；野外的', '1. Many farmers are working in the fields. 许多农民在田里干活。 2. He has become famous in his own field. 他在自己的领域里已经出名了。 3. The crowd cheered as the teams entered the field. 球队入场时观众们为之欢呼。 4. When Tom insulted the referee, he responded by ordering him off the field. 汤姆辱骂裁判员时,裁判员的反应是命令他退出场地。 5. She fielded the ball. 她把球接住了. 6. Just before sunset the peasants quit laboring in the field. 农民们直到日落方结束在田间的劳动。', '过去式: fielded 过去分词: fielded 现在分词: fielding 第三人称单数: fields');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('domestic', '[də\'mestɪk]', 'adj.家庭的；国内的；驯养的 n.佣人；家仆', '1. The store deals in objects of domestic utility. 那家商店出售家庭用品。 2. My value for domestic tranquility should much exceed theirs. 我应该远比他们重视家庭的平静生活。 3. Washington responded by freezing the price of domestic oil. 华盛顿作出的反应是冻结国内的石油价格。 4. We adopt an active attitude towards drawing on overseas fund to make up for domestic fund shortage. 我们采取积极的态度吸引海外资金以弥补国内资金短缺。 5. His domestics are all in years. 他的佣人全都上了年纪。', '副词: domestically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('auditorium', '[ˌɔːdɪ\'tɔːriəm]', 'n.礼堂；观众席', '1. The auditorium seats 3,000 people. 这个礼堂可坐三千人。 2. The stage is thrust forward into the auditorium. 舞台向前突出，伸入观众席。 3. The competition hasn\'t begun, but you can already hear the hubbub from the auditorium. 比赛还没开始，观众席上已经人声鼎沸了。', '名词复数: auditoriums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scholar', '[\'skɑːlər]', 'n.学者；获奖学金的学生', '1. He is a complete scholar. 他是个无懈可击的学者。 2. He is not so much a writer as a scholar. 与其说他是作家倒不如说他是学者。 3. He ranks high as a scholar. 他是第一流的学者。 4. She impressed me as a scholar. 她给我留下了学者的印象。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('height', '[haɪt]', 'n.高度；高处；顶点', '1. They looked down from a giddy height. 他们从令人眩晕的高度往下看。 2. His height makes him stand out in the crowd. 他身材高大，因此在人群中很突出。 3. The climber fell from a great height. 攀登者从极高的地方坠落下来。 4. Pop art was at its height in the early 1960s. 通俗艺术在二十世纪六十年代初最为流行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exclude', '[ɪk\'skluːd]', 'vt.排除；阻止；拒绝接受', '1. At this stage we cannot entirely exclude the possibility of staff cuts. 在目前这个阶段,我们还不能完全排除裁员的可能性。 2. I mean the last thing we would think about is to exclude the children from this plan. 我的意思是,我们绝不会考虑把孩子们排除在这个计划之外的。 3. Thick curtains help to exclude street noises. 厚窗帘有助于隔绝街上的噪音。 4. The court excluded the improperly obtained evidence. 法院不接受非正常渠道获得的证据', '形容词: excludable 名词: excludability 过去式: excluded 过去分词: excluded 现在分词: excluding 第三人称单数: excludes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brutal', '[\'bruːtl]', 'adj.野蛮的；残暴的', '1. The people have been kept down for years by a brutal regime. 人民多年遭受野蛮制度压迫。 2. The enemy made a brutal attack upon the villagers. 敌人对村民们进行了野蛮的攻击。 3. NATO\'s invasion of this independent country is a brutal violation of human rights. 北约对这个独立的国家的侵略是对人权的野蛮侵犯。 4. The brutal soldiers beat their prisoners ruthlessly. 残暴的士兵野蛮地抽打俘虏。', '副词: brutally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drill', '[drɪl]', 'n.钻孔机；钻子；反复操练；播种机 v.练习；钻孔；(军事)训练', '1. The dentist\'s drill made a lot of noise. 牙钻发出很大的噪音。 2. Jack used a drill to bore a hole in the wall above the fireplace. 杰克用钻子在壁炉上方的墙上钻孔。 3. Today\'s art lesson came to an abrupt end when the gongs sounded for a fire drill. 今天的美术课因火灾演习的铃声大作而突然结束。 4. You\'d better set a goal before you start the drill. 练习开始前，你最好设定一个目标。 5. Listen to the first paragraph, then let them drill in teams. 听第一段,然后分组练习。', '名词: driller 过去式: drilled 过去分词: drilled 现在分词: drilling 第三人称单数: drills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('punish', '[\'pʌnɪʃ]', 'vt.惩罚；粗暴对待 vi.处罚', '1. The teacher blazoned she would punish the bad student. 老师宣布她将惩罚那个坏学生。 2. Their teacher punished them for their rudeness. 老师因为他们态度粗鲁而责罚他们。 3. Dangerous driving should be severely punished. 危险驾驶应受严惩。 4. The teacher warned them that she would punish anyone who stepped out of line. 老师警告他们说谁要不守规矩就罚谁。 5. I have a mind to punish you for stealing a cookie. 我有意要处罚你偷饼干。', '形容词: punishable 名词: punishability 过去式: punished 过去分词: punished 现在分词: punishing 第三人称单数: punishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('detect', '[dɪ\'tekt]', 'v.发觉；察觉；探测', '1. Do I detect a tinge of irony? 我觉得这话有点儿像反话吧? 2. If you read between the lines, you can detect his contrived explanation. 在字里行间，你可以看出他牵强的解释。 3. I seemed to detect some anger in his voice. 我似乎在他的声音中听出一些怒气。 4. Small quantities of poison were detected in the dead man\'s stomach. 在死者胃中找到了少量的毒药。', '形容词: detectable 名词: detecter 过去式: detected 过去分词: detected 现在分词: detecting 第三人称单数: detects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thereby', '[ˌðer\'baɪ]', 'adv.因此；从而', '1. They paid cash, thereby avoiding interest charges. 他们付了现款，因此不必另外加息。 2. He became a citizen, thereby gaining the right to vote. 他成为公民，并因此获得了选举权。 3. I have never been to that city; thereby I don\'t know much about it. 我从未去过那座城市,因此对它不怎么熟悉。 4. Suppliers will lower the price to increase sales, thereby moving toward equilibrium. 供给者将降低价格以增加销售', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anything', '[\'eniθɪŋ]', 'pron.任何事；任何东西；重要事物 adv.在任何程度上', '1. If you remember anything at all, please let us know. 你要是想起什么来，就告诉我们。 2. The hotel was anything but satisfactory. 这家旅馆太不让人满意了。 3. Is there anything for me? 有东西给我吗？ 4. Anything will do to keep the door open. 只要能使门敞开着，什么东西都行。 5. He isn\'t anything like my first boss. 他一点也不像我第一个老板。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('confusion', '[kən\'fjuːʒən]', 'n.惶惑；混淆；混乱；不确定状态', '1. He gazed in confusion at the strange sight. 他惶惑地凝视着这种奇怪的景象。 2. This misprint led to great confusion. 这个印刷错误造成很大的混淆。 3. Words like\"believe\" and \"receive\" are a source of confusion in spelling. 诸如 believe和 receive 这样的词在拼写上容易混淆。 4. The most brilliant person may be mired in details and confusions. 即使是最聪明的人也会陷入琐事与混乱之中。', '形容词: confusional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wrap', '[ræp]', 'v.包；裹；覆盖；隐藏 n.围巾；披肩；包装材料', '1. You should wrap up the gift in a paper. 你应该把礼物用纸包好。 2. I wrapped the rug around the sick man\'s legs to keep him warm. 我用毯子把病人的腿包了起来，让他暖和一点儿。 3. Wrap the meat in foil before you cook it. 把肉用锡箔裹起来后再烧。 4. The lid is an aluminium-covered cork bung, over-covered with a tamper-evident shrink wrap. 盖子是铝覆盖软木邦，过覆盖篡改明显收缩包装。 5. Over her shoulders was thrown a much-mended wrap. 她的肩上搭着一件补了多次的围巾。', '过去式: wrapped/wrapt 过去分词: wrapped/wrapt 现在分词: wrapping 第三人称单数: wraps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lamb', '[læm]', 'n.小羊；羔羊肉；羔羊；温顺的人 vi.产羊羔', '1. The lamb had to be brought up by hand. 这只小羊要用奶瓶喂养。 2. The dying lamb fell, its legs flailing (about) helplessly. 小羊快要死了，倒在地上四条腿又踢又蹬。 3. Veal is young beef and lamb is a baby sheep. 小牛肉是小牛犊身上的肉，小羊肉是羔羊身上的肉。 4. The little lamb was caught by the wolf. 小羔羊被狼抓住了。 5. The sheep are lambing this week. 这个星期绵羊要产羔。', '过去式: lambed 过去分词: lambed 现在分词: lambing 第三人称单数: lambs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('equator', '[ɪ\'kweɪtər]', 'n.赤道', '1. The equator is an imaginary line. 赤道是一条实际上并不存在的线。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('globe', '[ɡloʊb]', 'n.地球；地球仪；球体；世界', '1. Magellan was the first person to circumnavigate the globe. 麦哲伦是第一个环球航行的人。 2. This plant can grow in many parts of the globe. 这种植物能在地球上许多地方生长。 3. A terrestrial globe is one that represents the earth. 地球仪是表现地球的器具。 4. This is hard to see without reference to a globe. 如果不参照着一个地球仪来看，这是很难理解的。', '过去式: globed 过去分词: globed 现在分词: globing 第三人称单数: globes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('badge', '[bædʒ]', 'n.象征；标记；徽章；证章 vt.授给 ... 徽章', '1. Chains are a badge of slavery. 锁链是奴役的标志。 2. The olive leaf is a badge of peace. 橄榄叶是和平的象征。 3. What is that badge on your lapel? 你翻领上的是什么徽章? 4. He was awarded a merit badge for his bravery in the battle. 他因为在战斗中的勇猛被授予一枚奖章。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nerve', '[nɜːrv]', 'n.神经；勇气；敏感处；叶脉；厚脸皮 v.鼓起勇气 （复）nerves: 神经紧张.', '1. A sensitive nerve in a tooth can cause great pain. 牙神经易受损伤，可产生巨痛。 2. You\'ll need plenty of nerve to sit beside him when he is driving. 他开车的时候，你得有足够的胆量才敢坐在他旁边。 3. I hit a nerve when I mentioned her dead mother. 当我提到她死去的母亲时, 我触到了她的伤心处。 4. Did he have the nerve to say that? 他竟有脸说这话吗？ 5. I nerved myself to face my accusers. 我下决心迎击指责我的人。', '过去式: nerved 过去分词: nerved 现在分词: nerving 第三人称单数: nerves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sheer', '[ʃɪr]', 'adj.极轻薄的；陡峭的；全然的 adv.垂直地 v.避开；转向', '1. Chiffon is a fabric of sheer silk or rayon. 薄绸是一种极薄的丝绸或人造丝织物。 2. It\'s very difficult to climb a sheer cliff. 攀登陡峭的悬崖是很困难的。 3. She played a trick on him out of sheer devilment. 她捉弄他完全是为了寻开心。 4. He\'s so impatient that waiting in queues is sheer purgatory for him. 他毫无耐性，对他来说排队等候完全是活受罪。 5. The ground dropped away sheer at our feet. 我们脚下的地面垂直地陷落下去。 6. When he saw me coming he sheered off in the opposite direction. 他一看到我过来，掉头就走了。', '副词: sheerly 比较级: sheerer 最高级: sheerest 名词: sheerness 过去式: sheered 过去分词: sheered 现在分词: sheering 第三人称单数: sheers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kingdom', '[\'kɪŋdəm]', 'n.王国；领域；界 Kingdom：天国.', '1. The ruler of a kingdom is designated a king. 王国的统治者称作国王。 2. The Calcite Mineral Kingdom addresses you today. 今天是方解石王国向你们问候。 3. This is the fight of the kingdom of the mind. 这是思想领域的斗争。 4. Language was considered a specific sphere, a fourth natural kingdom. 人们把语言看作一种特殊的领域，自然界的第四王国。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oppress', '[ə\'pres]', 'v.使烦恼；压迫', '1. Cares oppressed his spirits. 忧虑使他心情抑郁。 2. The king oppressed his people with terrible taxes and punishments. 国王以苛捐杂税和严刑来压迫人民。 3. Free governments do not oppress their people or attack other free nations. 自由政府不会压迫其人民或者攻击其他自由国家。', '名词: oppressor 过去式: oppressed 过去分词: oppressed 现在分词: oppressing 第三人称单数: oppresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acquire', '[ə\'kwaɪər]', 'vt.获得；学到；取得', '1. We should try to acquire good habits. 我们应该努力养成良好的习惯。 2. He will acquire the right to permanent residency here. 他将获得这里的永久居留权。 3. We hope to acquire the knowledge in the happiness. 我们希望在快乐中获得知识。 4. One can never acquire enough experience. 经验是永远学不足的。', '形容词: acquirable 名词: acquirer 过去式: acquired 过去分词: acquired 现在分词: acquiring 第三人称单数: acquires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preach', '[priːtʃ]', 'vt.讲道；说教 vi.传道；训诫', '1. The priest preached a sermon on the need of charity. 牧师在布道会上宣讲慈爱的必要。 2. Those people go around preaching revolution. 那些人到处宣扬革命。 3. Christ preached that we should love each other. 基督在布道中说人们应该互敬互爱。 4. She preached economy as the best means of solving the crisis. 她大力鼓吹节约是解决危机的关键。 5. The priest preached to the congregation about the Sermon on the Mount. 那位祭司就山中圣训向会众说教。', '副词: preachingly 过去式: preached 过去分词: preached 现在分词: preaching 第三人称单数: preaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('basis', '[\'beɪsɪs]', 'n.基础；根据；基底', '1. His research formed the basis of his new book. 他的研究成果是他这本新书的基础。 2. We drew this conclusion on the basis of experiments. 我们是在试验的基础上得出这个结论的。 3. What basis do you have for saying that? 你那样说有什么根据啊? 4. Rates of work are calculated on a weekly basis. 工资是以周为计算基准的.', '名词复数: bases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('company', '[\'kʌmpəni]', 'n.公司；商号；陪伴；同伴；客人；[军]连；一群 v.陪伴', '1. I work in a small company. 我在一家小公司工作。 2. The company doubled its size in nine years. 9年来这家公司的规模扩大了一倍。 3. The company has connections with a number of Japanese firms. 这家公司与几家日本商号有业务往来。 4. Don\'t mention it. I\'ve really enjoyed your company. 不必客气,有你的陪伴,我也很开心。 5. May fair winds company your safe return. 愿和风伴你平安归来。', '名词复数: companies 过去式: companied 过去分词: companied 现在分词: companying 第三人称单数: companies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expenditure', '[ɪk\'spendɪtʃər]', 'n.开支；消耗', '1. We must try our best to control our expenditure. 我们必须尽力控制开销。 2. The government intends to cut expenditure on arms. 政府打算削减军备开支。 3. Such a great task requires the expenditure of much money and time. 这么庞大的任务需要消耗许多的金钱和时间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prick', '[prɪk]', 'v.刺；扎；竖起；受责备 n.扎；刺；刺痛；<俚>蠢人', '1. The thorns of roses prick rather badly. 玫瑰刺刺得很痛。 2. I am afraid I have to prick your finger and take a drop of blood. 我恐怕不得不刺破你的手指，取一滴血。 3. She pricked herself on a needle. 她被针扎了一下。 4. The rabbit stopped suddenly, pricking up its ears. 兔子突然停下来，竖起自己的耳朵。 5. The needle left a prick in the tailor\'s finger. 裁缝的手指上有个针扎的孔。', '过去式: pricked 过去分词: pricked 现在分词: pricking 第三人称单数: pricks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('meantime', '[\'miːntaɪm]', 'adv.与此同时 n.同时；其间', '1. I continued working. Meantime, he went out shopping. 我继续工作。这期间他出去买东西。 2. The new software will be available in the spring. Meantime, users with problems can call our helpline. 今年春天,用户可以使用新的软件。与此同时,用户如有问题可致电我们的热线服务。 3. I like skiing and in the meantime, I know it is very dangerous. 我喜欢滑雪，同时也知道这非常危险。 4. You buy the fruits, in the meantime I\'ll cook breakfast. 你去买水果，同时我来做早餐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hierarchy', '[\'haɪərɑːrki]', 'n.等级制度；统治集团；[生]级系', '1. There is a hierarchy in all living creatures. 一切生物均可按等级分类。 2. It\'s not as if he was very important in the company hierarchy. 他在公司的领导层中似乎无多大权力。 3. pull silver', '名词复数: hierarchies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sorry', '[\'sɑːri]', 'adj.对不起的；抱歉的；难过的；遗憾的 int.对不起', '1. I\'m frightfully sorry, but I can\'t see you today. 太对不起了，我今天不能见你。 2. I\'m sorry to obtrude on you at such a time. 我很抱歉在这个时候打扰你。 3. Don\'t feel sorry about the broken glass. 别再为那打破的杯子难过了。 4. I\'m sorry he doesn\'t write more regularly. 遗憾的是他没能经常写信。 5. Sorry, we\'ve sold out of shirts in your size. 对不起，你这样尺寸的衬衣都卖完了。', '副词: sorrily 比较级: sorrier 最高级: sorriest 名词: sorriness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pearl', '[pɜːrl]', 'n.珍珠 v.(用珍珠)装饰；呈珍珠状 adj.珍珠般的', '1. The pearl sparkled in the moonlight. 那颗珍珠在月光下闪闪发光。 2. She wears a pearl necklace today. 今天她戴了一条珍珠项链。 3. Then there must be some pearl powder in it. 那么这里一定有一些珍珠粉。 4. The Riverview deluxe rooms of Pearl Haosheng Hotel with elegant decorative style are the best choice of you for business membership and sightseeing. 江城明珠豪生大酒店江景豪华房，装饰风格高贵典雅细节之处更令人不胜惊喜，是您商务会友及观光旅游的理想首选。', '过去式: pearled 过去分词: pearled 现在分词: pearling 第三人称单数: pearls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disappear', '[ˌdɪsə\'pɪr]', 'vi.消失；不见；失踪', '1. The sun disappeared behind a cloud. 太阳消失在一片云后面。 2. Many beautiful fish are fast disappearing because of the severe pollution. 因为污染严重，许多美丽的鱼类正在面临绝种。 3. My wallet has disappeared from the table. 我放在桌子上的钱包不见了。 4. I saw her step the street and disappear into the post-office. 我看见她在街上步行，进了邮局就不见了。', '名词: disappearance 过去式: disappeared 过去分词: disappeared 现在分词: disappearing 第三人称单数: disappears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dazzle', '[\'dæzl]', 'v.使眼花；使赞许 n.光辉', '1. His eyes dazzled before the strong light. 他面对强光头晕目眩。 2. She was dazzled by her sudden success. 突然的成功使她感到迷惘。 3. The diamond ring worn in her bridle hand\'s third finger dazzle against firelight. 她左手无名指上戴的钻石戒指在火光下闪闪发亮。 4. You will dazzle everyone you meet this week. 遇到的每个人都会为你倾倒。 5. The theatre was a dazzle of bright lights. 剧院是一片光芒耀眼的明亮灯光。', '副词: dazzlingly 名词: dazzler 过去式: dazzled 过去分词: dazzled 现在分词: dazzling 第三人称单数: dazzles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('opera', '[\'ɒpərə]', 'n.歌剧 n.挪威Opera软件公司的浏览器软件', '1. Have you heard the opera sung in French? 你听过用法语唱的这场歌剧吗？ 2. Opera houses were packed out whenever she was singing. 她一演唱剧院就满座。 3. That opera singer has good lungs. 那位歌剧演员声音宏亮。 4. The opera was quite stupendous. 这部歌剧很精彩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('embarrass', '[ɪm\'bærəs]', 'vt.使窘迫；使尴尬；使为难 vi.窘迫', '1. She dragged up that incident just to embarrass me. 她又扯起那件事故意想使我难堪。 2. He was embarrassed by many debts. 他被很多债务弄得焦灼不安。 3. She may embarrass you with her uncouth behavior. 她的粗野行为可能会让你尴尬。 4. You didn\'t embarrass me in the slightest. 你一点也没让我为难。 5. Eye contact may convey sincerity and attentiveness in Western cultures but too much eye contact may embarrass people in some Oriental cultures. 在西方文化，目光接触能传递真诚和关注，但太多的目光接触在某些东方文化中则令人窘迫。', '副词: embarrassedly 过去式: embarrassed 过去分词: embarrassed 现在分词: embarrassing 第三人称单数: embarrasses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('array', '[ə\'reɪ]', 'n.一系列；大批；数组；陈列，列队；盛装 vt.排列；部署；打扮', '1. The era also gave birth to a whole array of new social problems. 那个时代还产生了一系列新的社会问题。 2. We have quite an array of leather shoes. 我们有一大批各类皮鞋。 3. Today\'s vehicles offer an array of advanced safety features. 现在的汽车都提供了大量先进的安全设备。 4. Our troops were drawn up in battle array. 我们的部队已严阵以待。 5. I want to array this specimen mount in the display window. 我想把这个标本架放到橱窗里。', '过去式: arrayed 过去分词: arrayed 现在分词: arraying 第三人称单数: arrays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('successful', '[sək\'sesfl]', 'adj.成功的；圆满的', '1. She made a successful debut. 她初次登台获得成功。 2. He aims to be a successful writer. 他的目标是成为一个成功的作家。 3. They are highly successful in business. 他们经商非常成功。 4. We are confident of a successful outcome. 我们相信会有圆满的结果。', '副词: successfully 名词: successfulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intimate', '[\'ɪntɪmət]', 'adj.亲密的；私人的；关系紧密的 vt.暗示；透露 n.密友', '1. She was so kind as to forgive her intimate friend who had betrayed her when she was in a great difficulty. 她如此善良,竟能原谅在她处境最艰难时背叛她的挚友。 2. The magazine published intimate details of their affair. 这本杂志刊登出了他们恋情的私密细节。 3. Island communities commonly feel an intimate connection with the sea and with seafarers. 岛国的居民一般都会感觉自己与海洋和水手之间存在着紧密的联系。 4. He stated what others had only dared to intimate. 他说出了别人只敢暗示的话。 5. Sir Reginald was known to his intimates as \"Porky\". 雷金纳德爵士的至交都叫他“胖子”。', '副词: intimately 名词: intimateness 过去式: intimated 过去分词: intimated 现在分词: intimating 第三人称单数: intimates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coat', '[koʊt]', 'n.外套；上衣；层；表皮 vt.涂上；覆盖；包上', '1. You may hang your coat on the hook. 你可以把外套挂在钩子上。 2. She was wearing a woolen coat, with a cotton blouse underneath. 她外面穿了一件毛外套，里面穿一件棉布衬衫。 3. Jane bought a fur coat yesterday. 简昨天买了一件裘皮大衣。 4. One of the buttons has come off my coat. 我上衣上的一颗扣子掉了。 5. The bookshelves were coated with red paint. 书架上涂了一层红色的油漆。', '形容词: coated 过去式: coated 过去分词: coated 现在分词: coating 第三人称单数: coats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guard', '[ɡɑːrd]', 'v.看守；守卫；保卫；提防 n.警戒；哨兵；防护装置；警卫；【体】后卫', '1. He keeps a dog to guard the house. 他养一条狗看家。 2. The dog guarded the house against strangers. 狗守卫着房屋，不让陌生人进去。 3. Ten soldiers were detailed to guard the bridge. 十名战士被派去保卫那座桥梁。 4. You must guard against catching a cold. 你必须小心以防感冒。 5. Be on guard when somebody flatters you. 有人奉承你时，一定要当心。', '名词: guarder 过去式: guarded 过去分词: guarded 现在分词: guarding 第三人称单数: guards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('face', '[feɪs]', 'n.表面；脸；表情 v.面对；面向；朝', '1. A cut diamond has many faces. 经切割的钻石有很多晶面。 2. They disappeared from the face of the earth. 他们从地面上消失了。 3. The clowns pulled funny faces. 小丑扮出了可笑的鬼脸。 4. The sun was shining in our faces. 太阳光直射在我们脸上。 5. He faced the difficulty with courage. 他勇敢地面对困难。', '形容词: faceable 名词: facelessness 过去式: faced 过去分词: faced 现在分词: facing 第三人称单数: faces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('authentic', '[ɔː\'θentɪk]', 'adj.真正的；真实的；可信的；可靠的', '1. This is an authentic medieval sword. 这是一把真正的中世纪剑。 2. He found out the most authentic restaurants. 他找到了最正宗的餐馆。 3. The details of the costume were totally authentic. 这件古装的每个小地方都完全真实。 4. He\'s got an authentic letter by Shakespeare. 他弄到了一封莎士比亚的亲笔信。', '副词: authentically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('action', '[\'ækʃn]', 'n.行为；活动；措施；效用；交战；情节；事件；姿态；起诉；机能', '1. There is no denying that your action has affected her normal life. 不可否认,你的行为已经影响了她的正常生活。 2. After the security incident, you should create an action report that includes three simple goals. 这次安全事故后,你要撰写一个包括三个简单目标的活动报告。 3. The government finally took some actions because the public had been pressing for inquiry into the question. 由于公众一再坚持调查这一问题,政府终于采取了一些措施。 4. The medicine will not take action until two hours later. 这药在两小时後才会起作用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('learning', '[\'lɜːrnɪŋ]', 'n.学问；学识；学习 动词learn的现在分词.', '1. He made a display of his learning. 他夸耀自己有学问。 2. There is no royalroad to learning. 学无坦途，学问无捷径。 3. He earned a high reputation for his learning. 他在学识方面享有很高的声誉。 4. He has much learning, but he hides it in a napkin. 他学识渊博，可是并没有把它发挥出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('law', '[lɔː]', 'n.法律；法规；准则；起诉 v.起诉；打官司', '1. The law forbids stealing. 法律禁止盗窃。 2. Those who break the law are subjected to justice. 违法者要受到法律制裁。 3. The new law has received the royal assent. 新的法规已得到国王的批准。 4. The least possible sin is the law of man. 尽量少犯错误，这是人的准则；', '过去式: lawed 过去分词: lawed 现在分词: lawing 第三人称单数: laws');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refute', '[rɪ\'fjuːt]', 'vt.驳斥；反驳；驳倒', '1. As for the Flat Earth theory, I believe I could refute it. 至于地平学说，我相信我能驳斥它。 2. Historical facts refute such a fallacy. 历史事实驳斥了这种谎言。 3. He had hardly finished when someone rose to refute his points. 他还没全说完，就有人起来反驳他的论点。 4. Nothing could refute her testimony that the driver was drunk. 她关于那个司机已经喝醉的证词无可辩驳。', '形容词: refutable 副词: refutably 名词: refutability 过去式: refuted 过去分词: refuted 现在分词: refuting 第三人称单数: refutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peel', '[piːl]', 'n.果皮 vt.剥落；削皮 vi.脱皮；脱衣服', '1. She threw the banana peel into the trash can. 她将香蕉皮扔进垃圾筒。 2. It is said that the apple peel contains a lot of vitamins. 据说苹果皮富含维生素。 3. The paper was beginning to peel off the walls. 墙上的纸渐渐脱落了. 4. He likes to peel an apple before he eats it . 吃苹果前，他喜欢削皮。 5. He got sunburn and his skin began to peel. 他被日光灼伤后,皮肤开始脱落。', '过去式: peeled 过去分词: peeled 现在分词: peeling 第三人称单数: peels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tribe', '[traɪb]', 'n.部落；族；一伙人', '1. A council of elders governs the tribe. 有个叫长老会的组织治理这个部落。 2. Our tribe is under a curse. 我们的部落正受诅咒。 3. I have heard the cannibal tribe in stories. 我在故事里听说过食人部落。 4. That Indian man is a member of the neighbouring tribe. 那个印第安人是临近部落的成员。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('toe', '[toʊ]', 'n.脚趾；足尖 vt.趾触；趾踢 vi.踮着脚尖走 abbr.吨油当量（=Ton Oil Equivalent）', '1. Each foot has five toes. 每只脚有五个脚趾头。 2. He stepped on my toes. 他踩着了我的脚趾头。 3. I\'ve stubbed my toe on a rock. 我的脚趾碰到石头上了。 4. My boot is pressing against a blister on my toe. 我的靴子挤压了我脚趾上的水泡。 5. He toed the cigarette out. 他将香烟踩灭。 6. He toes out. 他踮着脚走了出去。', '过去式: toed 过去分词: toed 现在分词: toeing 第三人称单数: toes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seemingly', '[\'siːmɪŋli]', 'adv.表面上；似乎；看起来', '1. Any seemingly viable proposition will be tested by market research. 任何表面上可行的建议都要通过市场研究予以检验。 2. The utility, though seemingly rebuffed, in fact got what it wanted, or thereabouts. 公司虽然表面上遭到了挫败，实际上得到了它所要求的，或者相差不多的增额。 3. She plays with seemingly effortless skill. 她演奏得似乎毫不费力。 4. He is seemingly to have lost enthusiasm in reading. 他似乎在阅读上已经失去了热情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ashamed', '[ə\'ʃeɪmd]', 'adj.感到惭愧的；感到害臊的', '1. He is ashamed for his former dishonorable action. 他对他以前不光彩的行为感到羞愧。 2. He was ashamed that he had lied. 他很惭愧他说了谎。 3. As for you, you should feel ashamed. 至于你，你应该感到惭愧。 4. He jumped up,looking a little ashamed of himself. 他跳了起来，显得有点惭愧。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mask', '[mæsk]', 'n.伪装；面罩；面具；[计算机]掩码 v.掩饰；戴面具；遮盖', '1. They did so under the mask of charity. 他们是打着慈善的幌子这么做的。 2. He longed to throw off the mask of respectability. 他渴望丢掉那副道貌岸然的伪装。 3. Her sociable manner is really a mask for a very shy nature. 她那好交际的作风，实际上是她腼腆天性的伪装。 4. The bank robber wears a stocking mask. 那个抢劫银行的匪徒戴着长筒袜面罩。 5. Her smile masked true feelings. 她的微笑掩饰了她的感情。', '形容词: maskable 过去式: masked 过去分词: masked 现在分词: masking 第三人称单数: masks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('record', '[\'rekərd]', 'n.唱片；纪录；记载；经历；前科 v.记录；显示；(将声音等)录下', '1. As a result of this meeting, he made his first record. 由于这次会议,他制作了他的第一张唱片。 2. He did very well, but failed to break the record. 他做得很出色,但未破纪录。 3. She holds the world record for long distance swimming. 她保持着长距离游泳的世界纪录。 4. You should keep a record of your expenses. 你应该记下你的各项开支。 5. I recorded the score in a notebook. 我在笔记本上记下了分数。', '过去式: recorded 过去分词: recorded 现在分词: recording 第三人称单数: records');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('smuggle', '[\'smʌɡl]', 'v.走私；偷运；偷带', '1. They deny conspiring together to smuggle drugs. 他们否认共谋走私毒品。 2. Well, sir, when you smuggle things you lose them. 好了，先生，如果您走私东西，您就要失去这些东西。 3. He tried to smuggle diamonds into Japan. 他企图把钻石偷运进日本。 4. The syndicate collaborated with vice syndicates in the Mainland to smuggle women into Hong Kong for providing sex services. 该集团亦与内地的卖淫集团勾结，偷运女子来港卖淫。', '名词: smuggler 过去式: smuggled 过去分词: smuggled 现在分词: smuggling 第三人称单数: smuggles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coal', '[koʊl]', 'n.煤；木炭 vt.烧成炭；供应煤 vi.加煤；装煤', '1. He put a shovel of coal on to the fire. 他往火炉里加了一铲煤。 2. The country is rich in oil and coal. 这个国家石油和煤的资源丰富。 3. Coal can be converted to gas. 煤可以转化成煤气。 4. I\'m in charge of discharging a large amount of charcoal and coal at the coal mine. 我负责在煤矿卸一大堆木炭和煤。 5. The workers were coaling the ship when he came back. 当他回来的时候,工人们正在给船加煤。 6. Ships coal at Gibraltar. 船在直布罗陀上煤。', '过去式: coaled 过去分词: coaled 现在分词: coaling 第三人称单数: coals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assist', '[ə\'sɪst]', 'vt.帮助；协助 vi.帮助；出席 n.帮助；协助；助攻；协助的器械', '1. A team of nurses assisted the doctor in performing the operation. 一组护士协助医生施行手术。 2. I saw the angels standing near us, waiting to assist us, rejoicing in our accomplishments and joys. 我看见天使站在我们旁边,等着帮助我们,为我们的成就及喜悦而欢呼。 3. Sixty years ago, George Marshall came to this commencement and announced a plan to assist the nations of post-war Europe. 六十年前，乔治·马歇尔也是在这个地方的毕业典礼上，宣布了一个计划，帮助那些欧洲国家的战后建设。 4. I have too much work and no one to assist me 我工作太多,又没人协助我 5. I assisted in doing his homework. 我帮助他做功课。 6. The victims of earthquake need assist asap. 那些地震灾民需要立即援助。', '名词: assister 过去式: assisted 过去分词: assisted 现在分词: assisting 第三人称单数: assists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('corn', '[kɔːrn]', 'n.谷物；玉米；伤感平庸作品 v.形成(颗粒状)；腌；(用谷物)喂', '1. Corn shot up to seventy-three cents a bushel. 谷物猛涨到一蒲式耳七十三美分。 2. The corn grinds easily. 谷物容易磨成粉。 3. The ground was plowed and planted with corn. 地翻耕后种上了玉米。 4. There was an abundance of corn last year. 去年玉米丰收。 5. The farmer scattered corn for the chicken. 农夫撒谷子喂鸡。', '过去式: corned 过去分词: corned 现在分词: corning 第三人称单数: corns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rocket', '[\'rɑːkɪt]', 'n.火箭；芝麻菜；紫花南芥 v.猛涨；飞快地移动', '1. They sent a distress rocket. 他们发出了一枚呼救信号火箭。 2. A rocket manned by trained astronauts will launch soon. 载有受过训练的宇航员的火箭马上就要发射了。 3. Scientists have computed the probable course of the rocket. 科学家利用计算机计算了火箭可能运行的轨道。 4. She served a fillet of chicken with a rocket salad. 她做了一道鸡肉片拌芝蔴菜。 5. The price of oil has suddenly rocketed up. 石油价格突然飞涨。', '过去式: rocketed 过去分词: rocketed 现在分词: rocketing 第三人称单数: rockets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('essential', '[ɪ\'senʃl]', 'adj.本质的；必要的；重要的 n.要素；必需品', '1. This is of course still the essential method. 这当然仍是本质的方法。 2. This is desirable but by no means essential to the primary objective of validating mathematical models of aircraft behaviour. 对于验证飞机性能的数学模型这一主要目的来说，这是必须的，但决不是最本质的. 3. Concentration is essential if you want to do a good job. 如果你想把事情做好,专心是必要的。 4. Mass education is essential in promoting democracy. 民众教育对提倡民主是非常重要的。 5. What are the essentials of good teaching? 成功教学的要素是什么?', '副词: essentially 名词: essentiality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comparable', '[\'kɑːmpərəbl]', 'adj.可比较的；比得上的', '1. The achievements of an athlete and a writer are not comparable. 运动员的成就与作家的成就不能相提并论。 2. The sets of figures are not comparable. 这几组数字是不可比的。 3. Your achievements are comparable with his. 你的成绩可与他的相媲美。 4. His handwriting is not bad, but it\'s hardly comparable with yours. 他的书法不错，但是很难和你的相比。', '副词: comparably 名词: comparability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('barn', '[bɑːrn]', 'n.谷仓；牲口棚；车库；大而空荡的农屋', '1. The barn will store five tons of grain. 这个谷仓能放五吨粮食。 2. We took shelter from the storm in a barn. 我们在一个谷仓里躲避暴风雨。 3. The cows were feeding on hay in the barn. 母牛正在牲口棚里吃乾草呢。 4. Another barn has been built there. 另一个牲口棚建在那儿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('silence', '[\'saɪləns]', 'n.沉默；寂静 vt.使安静；使沉默', '1. We interpreted his silence as a refusal. 我们认为他的沉默是拒绝的表示。 2. His forceful arguments reduced his opponents to silence. 他那有力的论点驳得对手哑口无言。 3. There was nothing but silence in the room. 这间屋内声息全无，一片寂静。 4. A terrible silence descended upon the whole hall. 一阵可怕的寂静突然笼罩着整个厅堂。 5. The teacher tried to silence the pupils. 老师设法让学生们安静下来。', '过去式: silenced 过去分词: silenced 现在分词: silencing 第三人称单数: silences');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shutter', '[\'ʃʌtər]', 'n.百叶窗；遮门；快门 v.装以遮门；关上窗板；停业', '1. Open the shutter and see what the weather is like. 打开百叶窗，看看外面的天气如何。 2. She regained her balance and opened the shutter. 她重新站稳脚步，然后打开百叶窗。 3. This shutter device for fading a picture can be operated by hand. 这个使画面惭入的遮板装置可以用手操作。 4. He adjusted the shutter before taking a photo. 在照相前，他调整了快门。 5. The house was empty and shuttered. 这所房子是空的，窗板都关上了。', '过去式: shuttered 过去分词: shuttered 现在分词: shuttering 第三人称单数: shutters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('because', '[bɪ\'kɔːz]', 'conj.因为；由于', '1. I bought the house simply because it was large. 我购买了这房子，只是因为它面积大。 2. An argument was inevitable because they disliked each other so much. 争论是不可避免的，因为他们彼此非常厌恶。 3. I knew she was joking because she had a big grin on her face. 我知道她是在开玩笑，因为她脸上堆满笑容。 4. Many beautiful fish are fast disappearing because of the severe pollution. 因为污染严重，许多美丽的鱼类正在面临绝种。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('further', '[\'fɜːrðər]', 'adj.更远的 adv.进一步地；此外 v.促进；推动', '1. Our object is to further strengthen friendly relations between the two countries. 我们的目标是进一步加强两国之间的友好关系。 2. Further, it is important to consider the cost of repairs. 此外，重要的是要考虑修理费用。 3. They hoped the new venture would further the cause of cultural cooperation in Europe. 他们希望这个新项目将促进欧洲文化合作事业。 4. The ambitious young man used his friends to further his career. 这位野心勃勃的年轻人利用朋友来推动他的事业的发展。', '名词: furtherer 过去式: furthered 过去分词: furthered 现在分词: furthering 第三人称单数: furthers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hound', '[haʊnd]', 'n.猎狗；可鄙之人；追踪者；迷 vt.带猎犬狩猎；紧追；烦扰；催促', '1. They went hunting with a pack of hounds. 他们带一群猎狗去打猎。 2. The hound was quartering the woods. 这只猎犬在树林中四处搜寻猎物。 3. News hound sniffs the air. 狗仔队闻着空气里的味道。 4. My sister is a movie hound. 我妹妹是个影迷。 5. He has been hounded by his creditors in the past few months. 近几个月来，他一直被债主追债。', '名词: hounder 过去式: hounded 过去分词: hounded 现在分词: hounding 第三人称单数: hounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('supermarket', '[\'suːpərmɑːrkət]', 'n.超级市场', '1. A variety of food is sold at a supermarket. 超级市场各式各样的食物均有出售。 2. The supermarket is just in the corner of the street. 超市就在街角。 3. Another supermarket opened last week. 上星期又有一家超级市场开张了。 4. He usually trades at the nearby supermarket. 他通常在附近的超市购物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('salesman', '[\'seɪlzmən]', 'n.销售人员；推销员', '1. At first John served as a salesman. 起初约翰是一个销售人员。 2. The salesman\'s manner was abrupt to the point of rudeness. 这销售人员的态度唐突到粗鲁的程度。 3. The salesman cheated me into buying a fake. 那个推销员骗我买了假货。', '名词: salesmanship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pack', '[pæk]', 'n.一群；一副；包裹；一包 v.包装；解雇；塞满；收拾行李；佩戴', '1. The hare could find no safety, a pack of jackals had it in the wind. 野兔无处逃生,一群豺狗在追踪它。 2. He rounded on journalists, calling them \'a pack of vultures\'. 他突然对记者们大发雷霆，称他们是一帮贪婪的家伙。 3. A pack of cards has been spread on the table. 一副牌在桌被传播了。 4. Try to pair this card with one exactly the same from the other pack. 设法从另一副牌中取出一张和这张完全一样的牌。 5. In order to avoid any possible damage in transit, we would ask you to pack the goods in strong but small wooden cases. 为避免运送过程中的任何损坏,我方希望贵方用牢固且小巧的木箱来包装这些货物。', '形容词: packable 名词: packability 过去式: packed 过去分词: packed 现在分词: packing 第三人称单数: packs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('care', '[ker]', 'v.关心；担忧；照顾；喜爱；介意；倾向于；愿望；在乎 n.小心；照料；忧虑；注意；护理', '1. It makes me feel good that you care about me. 你关心我,我感到很高兴。 2. She will care for the children while I am away. 我不在的时候,她会照顾那些孩子。 3. He doesn\'t care for fish. 他不喜欢吃鱼。 4. I don\'t care whether or not she will attend the meeting. 她是否来参加会议,我不介意。 5. Owing to wet weather, motorists are advised to drive with extra care. 雨天路滑,请格外小心驾驶。', '过去式: cared 过去分词: cared 现在分词: caring 第三人称单数: cares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('technician', '[tek\'nɪʃn]', 'n.技术员；技师', '1. A technician on probation was hit by a piece of falling masonry. 一个见习技术员被建筑物上落下的一块石头砸着了。 2. They need one laboratory technician. 他们需要一名实验室技术员。 3. That technician is highly skilled. 那位技师技术很好。 4. He is an electrical technician by profession. 他的职业是电工技师。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('understand', '[ˌʌndər\'stænd]', 'v.懂得；明白；理解；认识到；听说；获悉', '1. He is trying his best to understand his meaning. 他正在尽力弄明白他的意思。 2. I don\'t understand what you\'re talking about. 我不明白你在说什么。 3. If you can\'t do it, I will understand. 如果你不会做这件事的话，我可以理解。 4. I don\'t fully understand his reasons for leaving. 我不完全理解他离开的理由。', '形容词: understandable 副词: understandably 名词: understandability 过去式: understood 过去分词: understood 现在分词: understanding 第三人称单数: understands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('castle', '[\'kæsl]', 'n.城堡 v.置于城堡中；(棋)移动王车易位', '1. A spirit haunts the castle. 幽灵常出没于古堡。 2. The mist eddied round the old castle. 薄雾在那座古老的城堡的周围打转转。 3. The castle has fallen into decay in the last100 years. 这座古堡在近100年里渐渐荒废了。 4. The prince lived in a large and beautiful castle. 王子住在一个美丽的大城堡里。', '过去式: castled 过去分词: castled 现在分词: castling 第三人称单数: castles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dealer', '[\'diːlər]', 'n.商人；经销商；发牌者；毒品贩子', '1. The dealer was slavering over some precious stones. 那商人对一些宝石垂涎欲滴。 2. She beat the dealer down to a much better price. 她跟商人杀到一个很合适的价位。 3. The book dealer would not break the set. 这个图书经销商不会打破规定。 4. The dealer was shuffling the cards. 发牌者正在洗牌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strengthen', '[\'streŋθn]', 'v.加强；变坚固', '1. He has been brought in to strengthen the defence. 已请他来加强后卫力量。 2. We will strengthen the protection of wet land. 我们将加强湿地保护。 3. Every effort was made to strengthen unity. 大家尽力加强团结。 4. The current strengthened as we moved down the river. 我们顺流而下时，水流更急了。', '名词: strengthener 过去式: strengthened 过去分词: strengthened 现在分词: strengthening 第三人称单数: strengthens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('idiom', '[\'ɪdiəm]', 'n.成语；惯用语；方言；风格；特色', '1. This idiom cannot be translated literally. 这个成语无法照字面翻译。 2. From that story comes the idiom \"Draw a snake and add feet to it\". “画蛇添足”这个成语就是从这个故事来的。 3. \"Let the cat out of the bag\" is an idiom meaning to tell a secret by mistake. “让猫从袋子里跑出来”是惯用语，意思是无意中泄露秘密。 4. He spoke in the idiom of the New England countryside. 他讲新英格兰乡下的方言。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arrogant', '[\'ærəɡənt]', 'adj.傲慢的；自大的', '1. One should never be arrogant even when he is at his best. 一个人在最得意时也不应傲慢。 2. Well as he does in study, he is not arrogant. 虽然他功课很好，却一点都不傲慢。 3. It\'s arrogant of you to say that. 你竟然那样说，未免太自大了。 4. He is an arrogant man. 他是一个自高自大的人。', '副词: arrogantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consumption', '[kən\'sʌmpʃn]', 'n.消费；消耗；肺痨', '1. The government encourages individual consumption. 政府鼓励个人消费。 2. Internet shopping is a new way of consumption. 网上购物是当今消费的一种新途径。 3. The meat was condemned as unfit for human consumption. 这种肉已宣布不适宜人们食用。 4. The car scored well in fuel consumption. 那部汽车在燃料消耗方面获得好评。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('solar', '[\'soʊlər]', 'adj.太阳的；太阳能的', '1. The sun is the center of our solar system. 太阳是太阳系的中心 2. Solar irradiance decreases towards the poles. 太阳辐照率向两极递减。 3. The solar cell can convert the energy of sunlight into electric energy. 太阳能电池能把阳光的能量转化为电能。 4. The artificial heart is operated from solar cells. 人工心脏是由太阳能电池驱动的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enemy', '[\'enəmi]', 'n.敌人；敌军；有害物', '1. The city is held by the enemy. 这座城市已被敌人占领。 2. The enemy was forced to retreat. 敌人被迫撤退。 3. This defeat was a powerful blow to the enemy. 这次失败是对敌人的有力的打击。 4. In a frenzy of hate he killed his enemy. 在一阵痛恨的狂乱中，他杀死了敌人。', '名词复数: enemies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('implication', '[ˌɪmplɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.牵连；含意；暗示；卷入', '1. His implication in the crime was obvious to all. 大家都清楚他和这一罪行有牵连。 2. The trial resulted in the implication of several major figures in the organization. 审讯结果表明这个组织中几个主要人物都牵连在案。 3. He has not actually realized the full implication. 他还没有真正认识到全部含意。 4. The new report has far-reaching implications for the future of broadcasting. 这一新报告对广播业的前途有些意味深长的暗示。', '形容词: implicative 副词: implicatively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Thanksgiving', '[ˌθæŋks\'ɡɪvɪŋ]', 'n.感恩节', '1. We always have turkey for our Thanksgiving meal. 我们在感恩节总是吃火鸡。 2. Thanksgiving is a movable holiday. 感恩节的日期每年不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fortunate', '[\'fɔːrtʃənət]', 'adj.幸运的；侥幸的；带来幸运的', '1. It\'s fortunate you didn\'t forget. 幸好你没忘。 2. The girl was fortunate enough to have her mother as a bosom friend. 这个女孩非常幸运，她的妈妈是她的知心朋友。 3. The couple forfeited their independence in order to help those less fortunate. 这对夫妇把富裕出的钱都拿出来帮助那些受难的人。 4. It is fortunate that the tanker did not leak. 庆幸的是，油罐车没有发生泄漏。', '副词: fortunately 名词: fortunateness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('either', '[\'iðər]', 'adj.任一的；两方的 pron.任一 adv.也（用于否定句中） conj.或者（常用于either...or...的结构中）', '1. The thief was put in the police car with a policeman on either side of him. 窃贼被送到警车上，身旁各坐着一个警察。 2. You may take either of the roads. 两条路你随便走哪一条。 3. It\'s not as heavy, either. 这也不那么重。 4. If you do not go, I shall not go either. 你不去，我也不去。 5. I will go on business either this week or next week. 我将在这星期或下星期出差。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('daughter', '[\'dɔːtər]', 'n.女儿；子代 adj.女儿的；女儿似的', '1. Jill is my eldest daughter. 吉尔是我的长女。 2. The death of their daughter was a cruel blow. 女儿的死对他们是一个残酷的打击。 3. She spoke as a true daughter of the city. 她讲起话来真像来自这个城市的。 4. His unkindness to his daughter came home to roost. 他对女儿的刻薄得到了恶报。', '形容词: daughterly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cosmic', '[\'kɑːzmɪk]', 'adj.宇宙的；广大无边的；无限的', '1. I have mystical visions and cosmic vibrations. 我有神秘的幻觉和宇宙的震波。 2. I\'m pure, so I\'m more in touch with cosmic forces. 因为我纯洁，所以我能更好的接触宇宙的力量。', '副词: cosmically 异体字: cosmical');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('style', '[staɪl]', 'n.文体；风格；式样；时尚；类型', '1. The letter is written in formal style. 这封信是用正式文体写的。 2. I wouldn\'t tell lies to you; that\'s not my style. 我不会跟你撒谎，那不是我的风格。 3. The style of this skirt is just in season. 这条裙子的款式正当时令。 4. Her clothes are always in style. 她的衣服总是很时髦。', '名词: styler 过去式: styled 过去分词: styled 现在分词: styling 第三人称单数: styles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stretch', '[stretʃ]', 'v.伸展；延伸；张开；夸大 n.伸展；张开；弹性；一段时间；<俚>刑期 adj.可伸缩的', '1. Vast meadows stretch to the east. 辽阔的草场向东伸展。 2. She stretched across the table for the butter. 她探身去取放在餐桌对面的黄油。 3. The landscape seemed to stretch into infinity. 风景似乎延伸到了无穷远处。 4. Feeling intense fellowship with all human beings, she wished to throw herself into their arms, thinking that they would stretch them out to receive her. 她对所有的人怀着亲如手足的感情，她希望投身于他们的怀抱，以为他们会张开双臂接纳她。 5. I got out of the bed and had a good stretch. 我起床后舒服地伸了个懒腰。', '形容词: stretchable 名词: stretchability 过去式: stretched 过去分词: stretched 现在分词: stretching 第三人称单数: stretches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sneeze', '[sniːz]', 'n.喷嚏 vi.打喷嚏', '1. A baby\'s sneeze is not very loud. 婴儿的喷嚏不太响。 2. She let out a loud sneeze. 她打了一个很响的喷嚏。 3. The dust made him sneeze. 灰尘使他打了个喷嚏。 4. The pepper in the food caused me to sneeze. 这食物中的胡椒味儿呛得我直打喷嚏。', '形容词: sneezy 名词: sneezer 过去式: sneezed 过去分词: sneezed 现在分词: sneezing 第三人称单数: sneezes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bull', '[bʊl]', 'n.公牛；股市看涨的人；<俚>警察 n.荒谬的话 n.教皇诏书 adj.公牛的；鲁莽的', '1. The bull bellowed angrily. 公牛怒吼起来。 2. His bull will come to serve our cows tomorrow. 明天我们用他的公牛与我们的母牛配种。 3. A bull market is a situation in which share prices are rising. 牛市是指股价不断攀升的行情。 4. He likes to throw the bull. 他喜欢吹牛。 5. The pope issued a bull declaring that abortion was not approved by the church. 教皇发布训令，宣布堕胎不被教堂认可。 6. Still another depicted Europa deceived by Jupiter under the disguise of a bull. 再一幅是描写欧罗巴尼如何被化身成公牛的朱庇特所欺骗。', '过去式: bulled 过去分词: bulled 现在分词: bulling 第三人称单数: bulls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('entry', '[\'entri]', 'n.进入；进入权；入口；条目', '1. He pretended not to observe our entry. 他装作没有看见我们进来。 2. The people without a ticket are denied entry. 没有票的人不许入内。 3. He has applied for an entry visa. 他已申请入境签证。 4. You can leave your umbrella in the entry. 雨伞可放在入口处。', '名词复数: entries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shore', '[ʃɔːr]', 'n.岸；滨', '1. The breakers came tumbling onto the shore. 浪涛滚滚而来拍打著岸边。 2. They anchored their ship off the shore. 他们在滨外抛锚泊船。', '过去式: shored 过去分词: shored 现在分词: shoring 第三人称单数: shores');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sovereign', '[\'sɑːvrən]', 'n.元首；君主；最高统治者；金镑 adj.具有主权的；至高无上的；极好的', '1. The sovereign completely recovered from his illness. 元首完全自病中复原了。 2. No earthly sovereign can do what he pleases. 没有一个世间君王可以为所欲为。 3. A sovereign fell, bright and new, on the soft pile of the tablecloth. 一枚金镑，锃亮而崭新，落在厚实柔软的桌布上。 4. Morocco is a sovereign independent monarchy. 摩洛哥是个有主权而独立的君主国。', '副词: sovereignly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('volleyball', '[\'vɑːlibɔːl]', 'n.排球；排球运动', '1. Volleyball is a team game. 排球是一项要求全队默契配合的运动。 2. We are going to play neither basketball nor volleyball. 我们既不将打篮球也不将打排球。 3. Their team really whipped ours at volleyball. 他们的排球队彻底击败了我们队。 4. On the whole, I find volleyball more interesting. 总的说来,我认为排球运动更有趣。', '名词: volleyballer');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yard', '[jɑːrd]', 'n.院子；庭院 n.码(长度单位)', '1. I was out in the back yard splitting logs. 我那时正在后院劈柴。 2. We planted some elms in the yard. 我们在院子里种了一些榆树。 3. Her carriage was the most beautiful one in the yard. 她的马车是院子里最漂亮的。 4. He parked his car in the yard. 他把车停在院子里。 5. Three feet make one yard. 三英尺为一码。', '过去式: yarded 过去分词: yarded 现在分词: yarding 第三人称单数: yards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('their', '[ðer]', 'adj.他们的；她们的；它们的', '1. They washed their faces. 他们洗了脸。 2. Children depend on their parents for food and clothing. 小孩依赖他们的父母供给衣食。 3. Young mothers are gushing over their babies. 年轻的母亲滔滔不绝地谈论她们的婴儿。 4. We have no idea how the birds find their way. 我们不知道这些鸟如何找到它们的路。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('orient', '[\'ɔːriənt]', 'n.东方；亚洲 adj.东方的 vt.使适应；使…朝向；定 ... 的方位', '1. They love paintings from the Orient. 他们喜欢来自东方的绘画。 2. China is the biggest country in the orient. 中国是东方最大的国家。 3. The idea of cantilever construction is ancient in the Orient. 在亚洲古代就已实行过悬臂施工。 4. The vase seems to have an orient origin. 这花瓶好像来自东方。 5. I need some time to orient my thinking. 我需要一些时间来使我的思想适应。', '过去式: oriented 过去分词: oriented 现在分词: orienting 第三人称单数: orients');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wretched', '[\'retʃɪd]', 'adj.可怜的；不幸的；悲惨的；质量差的；恶劣的；卑鄙的', '1. She looked wretched and forlorn, despairing of the arrival of a friend who had promised to meet her. 她看上去又可怜又孤独，对于答应来看她的朋友的到来已不抱希望。 2. The wretched man lost all his money. 这个不幸的男人丢了所有的钱。 3. She lamented to us about her wretched lot. 她向我们哀叹自己悲惨的遭遇。 4. I cannot picture myself in more wretched condition. 我想像不出一个比这更悲惨的境地了。', '副词: wretchedly 比较级: wretcheder 最高级: wretchedest 名词: wretchedness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clergy', '[\'klɜːrdʒi]', 'n.[总称]牧师；神职人员', '1. The clergy were sacred beings in Miss Ainley\'s eyes. 在安利小姐看来，牧师都是圣人。 2. I could heartily wish that more of our country clergy would follow this example. 我衷心希望，我国有更多的牧师效法这个榜样。 3. Prior to the law\'s enactment, most of the Danish clergy opposed it. 在通过该法规之前，多数丹麦神职人员反对此法规。 4. The superior clergy and a small remnant of other educated men read and wrote Latin. 上等的神职人员和一小部分残余的其他受过教育的人使用拉丁语读写。', '名词复数: clergies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('basic', '[\'beɪsɪk]', 'adj.基本的；基础的；初级的；含硅少的 n.基础；根本；[计]BASIC语言', '1. The family is the basic unit of society. 家庭是社会的基本单位。 2. The right to work is a basic right of the citizens. 劳动权是公民的一项基本权利。 3. Food, clothing and shelter are all basic necessities of life. 衣、 食、 住所是生活的基本必需品。 4. Basic research is of great importance in all scientific fields. 在各个科学领域里,基础研究是非常重要的。 5. His research formed the basic of his new book. 他的研究成果构成了这本新书的基础。', '副词: basically 名词: basicity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('particle', '[\'pɑːrtɪkl]', 'n.颗粒；微粒；极小量；质点；粒子；[语]小品词', '1. We can see the dust particles floating in the sunlight clearly. 我们可以很清楚地看到阳光下的灰尘颗粒。 2. An atom is the smallest indivisible particle of matter. 原子是最小的不可分的物质微粒。 3. There wasn\'t a particle of truth in what he said. 他说的没有一点真话。 4. The particle is displaced in a flow domain. 这质点在流动区域内运动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('giant', '[\'dʒaɪənt]', 'n.巨人；巨物；大公司 adj.巨大的', '1. The hero smote the giant with his sword. 英雄用剑猛劈巨人。 2. Shakespeare is a giant among writers. 莎士比亚是作家中的大文豪。 3. As we all know,Philips is the Dutch elctronics giant. 众所周知,飞利浦是荷兰电子业巨头。 4. That is one small step for a man, but one giant leap for mankind. 对于个人来说那是小小的一步,但对于整个人类来说却是一次巨大的飞越。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('continent', '[\'kɒntɪnənt]', 'n.大陆；洲；(the Continent)欧洲大陆', '1. The discovery of the new continent is usually referred to Columbus. 人们通常认为新大陆是哥伦布发现的。 2. There are seven continents in the world. 世界上有七大洲。 3. Asia is the largest continent on Earth. 亚洲是地球上最大的洲。 4. Many people embark at Dover for the Continent. 许多前往欧洲大陆的人都在多佛搭船。', '副词: continently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('execute', '[\'eksɪkjuːt]', 'vt.执行；实行；处决；完成', '1. Congress makes the laws; the President executes them. 国会制定法律，总统执行法律。 2. We then execute the code that we want to test. 接下来,我们执行我们要测试的代码。 3. Now that we have made the decision, we may execute the scheme as previously agreed. 既然我们已经做了决定,我们就可以实行既定方案了。 4. They executed the king. 他们把国王处决了。', '形容词: executable 名词: executer 过去式: executed 过去分词: executed 现在分词: executing 第三人称单数: executes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cure', '[kjʊr]', 'n.治疗；治愈；疗法；对策 v.治愈；治疗；纠正', '1. There is no effective cure for colds except rest. 除了多休息,没有有效的方法可以治疗感冒。 2. There is still no cure for the common cold. 目前仍没有治愈感冒的良药。 3. The doctor claimed to have discovered a cure for the disease. 这个医生声称找到治愈那个疾病的疗法。 4. The cure for stress lies in learning to relax. 消除紧张的方法在于学会放松。 5. When I left the hospital I was completely cured. 出院时，我已经完全痊愈了。', '形容词: cureless 名词: curer 过去式: cured 过去分词: cured 现在分词: curing 第三人称单数: cures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('temper', '[\'tempər]', 'n.脾气；性情 vt.使缓和；调和；锻炼', '1. He slammed the door in a temper. 他生气地摔门。 2. You should learn to keep your temper under control. 你应该学会控制自己的脾气。 3. They are of congenial temper. 他们的性情相投。 4. If you temper criticism with reason,everyone can obey you. 如果以说理来缓和批评，谁都会服从你。', '形容词: temperable 名词: temperability 过去式: tempered 过去分词: tempered 现在分词: tempering 第三人称单数: tempers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('angry', '[\'æŋɡri]', 'adj.生气的；愤怒的；（伤口等）肿痛的，发炎的；（天空或海洋）天昏地暗的，狂风暴雨的', '1. His imperious look makes us angry. 他那飞扬跋扈的样子令我们生气。 2. Don\'t be angry over such trivial matters. 别为这些琐事生气。 3. He shouts when he gets angry, as is often the case. 他生气时就大叫，这是常有的情形。 4. There was an angry squall from the bedroom. 卧室里传出一声愤怒的喊叫。', '比较级: angrier 最高级: angriest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mischief', '[\'mɪstʃɪf]', 'n.淘气；恶作剧；捣蛋鬼；损害；伤害', '1. I try to keep the boy out of mischief. 我尽量不让这个男孩胡闹。 2. There was a glint of mischief in her eyes. 她的眼中闪过了一丝调皮。 3. Those boys are brewing mischief. 那些孩子正在搞恶作剧。 4. The child was a mischief in school. 这孩子在学校是个淘气鬼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('concession', '[kən\'seʃn]', 'n.让步；特许权；租界；妥协', '1. I hope you can make some concession. 我希望你能做些让步。 2. I must make a concession to him. 我必须对他让步。 3. They interpreted her silence as concession. 他们把她的沈默解释为让步。 4. He has an ice-cream concession in the subway station. 他在地铁站拥有一家冰淇淋分店。', '形容词: concessional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guidance', '[\'ɡaɪdns]', 'n.指导；引导；导航', '1. Under his guidance, we finished the work smoothly. 在他的指导下，我们顺利地完成了工作。 2. She is a marriage guidance counselor. 她是婚姻问题的顾问。 3. Religion provides many people with guidance. 宗教为很多人起到引导的作用。 4. We should not do anything under the guidance of instincts. 我们不应该凭着直觉做事情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('TV', '[ˌtiː\'viː]', 'abbr.(=television) 电视；电视机', '1. There was no sale for black and white TV sets. 黑白电视机没有销路。 2. We sold these TV sets at rock-bottom prices. 我们以最低价出售了这些电视机。', '名词复数: TVs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('temple', '[\'templ]', 'n.神殿；寺院；庙宇 n.太阳穴，鬓角', '1. The heathen temple was torn down by a crowd of religions fanatics. 异教徒的神殿被一群宗教狂热分子拆除了。 2. He who does good comes to the temple gate, he who loves reaches the shrine. 行善者站在神殿门口，博爱者步入殿堂。 3. We reached the temple through an unfrequented mountain track. 我们沿着一条人迹罕至的小径到达了寺庙。 4. There is a large mural in the temple. 那个寺院里有一幅很大的壁画。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sir', '[sɜːr]', 'n. 先生； 阁下 Sir n. （用于姓名前） ... 爵士', '1. Sir Peter was raised to the peerage. 彼得先生被封为贵族。 2. Maybe you could take a seat in the lobby,sir. 或许您可以在大堂休息一下，先生。 3. I am heated and excited, sir, I know I am. 我真又恼火又生气，阁下，我知道我实在气不过。 4. But Sir Tim remains optimistic. 但迪姆阁下保持着他的乐观态度。 5. Sir Willoughby restrained a bound of his body. 威洛比爵士拼命遏制自己身体的跳动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('everyone', '[\'evriwʌn]', 'pron.每人；人人', '1. On this job everyone works straight-time. 在这项工作中，每人干满正常工作时间。 2. The ruling was not fair to everyone. 这项裁决并非对每人都公正。 3. Everyone should be guarded by legal barricades. 人人都应受法律保障。 4. The justice of these remarks was clear to everyone. 人人都明白这些话是公正的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intermittent', '[ˌɪntər\'mɪtənt]', 'adj.间歇的；断断续续的', '1. They saw the intermittent flashes from a lighthouse. 他们看见了灯塔发出一闪一灭的光。 2. He has intermittent bursts of interest. 他的兴趣是一阵阵的。 3. She suffered from intermittent headache. 她患间歇性头痛。 4. There was intermittent debate about. 有过断断续续的辩论。', '副词: intermittently 名词: intermittence');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bronze', '[brɑːnz]', 'n.青铜；青铜色；青铜制品；铜牌 adj.青铜制的；青铜色的 vt.使成青铜色', '1. The statue is made of bronze. 这座雕像是青铜铸成。 2. We fuse copper and tin to make bronze. 我们把铜和锡熔制成青铜。 3. The woods today are burnished bronze. 今天的树林是一片发亮的青铜色。 4. The sanctuary lamp and the metal furniture were bronze. 圣灯和一切金属器物都是青铜制品。 5. The sculpture was a bronze cast. 这个雕塑是青铜铸成的 6. His face had been bronzed by the sun. 他的脸被太阳晒成古铜色。', '形容词: bronzy 名词: bronzer 过去式: bronzed 过去分词: bronzed 现在分词: bronzing 第三人称单数: bronzes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('executive', '[ɪg\'zɛkjətɪv]', 'adj.行政的；决策的；经营的；[计算机]执行指令 n.行政主管；行政部门；决策者', '1. The executive manager tossed out my application. 行政经理拒绝了我的申请。 2. I was allowed to sit in on an executive meeting. 我获准列席一次行政会议。 3. He is on the executive committee. 他是该执行委员会委员。 4. An executive should be experienced in administration. 一个管理者应有行政管理的经验。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('holder', '[\'hoʊldər]', 'n.持有者；支持物', '1. He is a holder of an insurance policy. 他是保险单持有人。 2. She is a Brritish passport holder. 她持有英国护照。 3. Season- ticket holder will receive a refund if their train is cancelled. 定期车票持有者在其车次被取消时可获得退款。 4. Debenture holder has priority over ordinary shareholder . 债券持有人比普通股东享有优先权。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intend', '[ɪn\'tend]', 'vt.想要；打算；意指', '1. I haven\'t been to the exhibition, neither do I intend to go. 我还没有看展览会,我也不想去。 2. My husband trusts me and I don\'t intend to break that trust 我的丈夫信任我,所以我不想失去这种信任 3. I\'ve chosen the main actors and we intend to put it on next January. 我已经选好了主要演员,打算明年一月上演这出戏。 4. How long do you intend to stop with the firm? 你打算还为公司工作多久？', '过去式: intended 过去分词: intended 现在分词: intending 第三人称单数: intends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('activate', '[\'æktɪveɪt]', 'v.激活；使活动；起动', '1. You can activate the system by buttons or voice recognition. 你可以通过按钮或者声音识别来激活系统。 2. The burglar alarm was activated by mistake. 防盗铃误响了。 3. I think if you flip the blue switch near the bottom it will activate the air conditioner. 我想，如果你把下方的蓝色开关轻轻地推上，冷气就会出来了。 4. These push buttons can activate the elevator. 这些按钮能启动电梯。', '名词: activation 过去式: activated 过去分词: activated 现在分词: activating 第三人称单数: activates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oval', '[\'oʊvl]', 'adj.卵形的；椭圆形的 n.椭圆；椭圆形跑道', '1. There are many oval stones at the bottom of the stream. 在小河底上有许多卵形的石头。 2. The mirror is oval. 镜子是椭圆的。 3. The path of the earth around the sun is oval. 地球围绕太阳公转的轨道是椭圆形的。 4. He hair framed her face in a gentle oval. 她的头发把她的脸蛋勾勒成椭圆形。', '副词: ovally 名词: ovalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('absent', '[\'æbsənt]', 'adj.缺席的；不在的；缺乏的 vt.使缺席', '1. Professor Li is absent, I will take the lesson in the place of him. 李教授不在，我替他上课。 2. Many students were absent, notably the monitor. 许多学生缺席，特别是连班长也没来。 3. You should not be absent from class. 你不应当旷课。 4. Before such experiments, humans thought language skills were absent from the animal kingdom. 在做这些实验前,人们认为动物王国缺乏语言技能。 5. Why did you absent yourself from school yesterday? 昨天你为何不到校?', '副词: absently 过去式: absented 过去分词: absented 现在分词: absenting 第三人称单数: absents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('come', '[kʌm]', 'v.来；来到；来取、来拿；成为；达到；接近；摆出 ... 的样子；处于（某个位置）', '1. The train slowly came to the station. 火车缓缓地进站。 2. He will come on time even though it rains. 即使下雨，他还是会准时来的。 3. They came to a river. 他们来到河边。 4. I\'ve come for my book. 我来拿我的书。', '过去式: came 过去分词: come 现在分词: coming 第三人称单数: comes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sunshine', '[\'sʌnʃaɪn]', 'n.阳光；晴天', '1. Dewdrops shine brightly in the sunshine. 露珠在阳光下闪闪发光。 2. I saw her basking in the sunshine. 我看到她在阳光下晒太阳。 3. The water soon evaporated in the sunshine. 水在阳光下不久就蒸发了。 4. The petals of many flowers expand in the sunshine. 许多花的花瓣在阳光中绽放。', '形容词: sunshiny');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forever', '[fər\'evər]', 'adv.永远', '1. This terrible event is etched forever in my memory. 这一可怕事件永远深深地印刻在我的记忆中。 2. The vassal swore that he would be loyal to the king forever. 这位封臣宣誓他将永远忠诚于国王。 3. The lovers promised to be faithful forever. 这对情人互相许诺永不变心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('survive', '[sər\'vaɪv]', 'vt.幸免于难；存活；艰难度过；比 ... 活得长 vi.活着；继续存在', '1. She was the only one to survive the crash. 她是这次飞机失事的唯一幸存者。 2. These birds are able to survive the perils of the Arctic winter. 这些鸟能在北极寒冷的冬天里生存。 3. I don\'t know how I ever survived high school. 我都不知道我是怎样熬过高中那段岁月的。 4. Santos is survived by his wife of 49 years. 桑托斯的妻子比他多活了49年。 5. You need to be tough to survive in the jungle. 要在丛林中活下来就要有坚忍不拔的意志。', '名词: survivor 过去式: survived 过去分词: survived 现在分词: surviving 第三人称单数: survives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sock', '[sɑːk]', 'n.短袜', '1. There is a hole in my sock. 我的袜子上有个洞。 2. He selected a pair of socks to match his suit. 他挑选了一双与他衣服相配的短袜。', '过去式: socked 过去分词: socked 现在分词: socking 第三人称单数: socks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('situation', '[ˌsɪtʃu\'eɪʃn]', 'n.形势；局面；位置；职位；处境；状况', '1. The overall situation is worsening. 整体形势在日益恶化。 2. The economic situation is now different. 现在经济形势不同了。 3. You dealt with an awkward situation very tactfully. 你很巧妙地处理了一个困难的局面。 4. The house is in a good situation at the top of the hill. 这座房子在山上的一个好位置上。', '形容词: situational 副词: situationally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wine', '[waɪn]', 'n.葡萄酒；酒；紫红色；使人沉醉的东西 vi.喝酒 vt.请 ... 喝酒 adj.深红色的', '1. He likes to drink red wine at supper. 他喜欢在晚饭时喝红葡萄酒。 2. The wine is left to mature in oak barrels. 葡萄酒在橡木桶中陈酿。 3. He drank the wine slowly, savoring every drop. 他慢慢地喝着酒，细细品尝着每滴酒的滋味。 4. This deeply coloured red wine is a blend of 4 varieties. 由四款葡萄混酿而成，酒液呈深紫红色。 5. I used to wine with my meals. 我过去吃饭时常常配点酒喝。 6. Our hosts wined and dined us very well. 主人设酒宴盛情款待我们。', '过去式: wined 过去分词: wined 现在分词: wining 第三人称单数: wines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pink', '[pɪŋk]', 'adj.粉红色的 n.粉红色', '1. She carried a spray of pink roses. 她拿著一簇粉红色的玫瑰花。 2. Write your name and address on this pink slip. 在这张粉红色纸条上写下你的姓名和地址。 3. The sunset has tinted the sky with pink. 落日把天空染成了粉红色。 4. Pink is her favorite color. 粉红色是她最喜欢的颜色。', '比较级: pinker 最高级: pinkest 名词: pinkness 过去式: pinked 过去分词: pinked 现在分词: pinking 第三人称单数: pinks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weed', '[wiːd]', 'n.杂草；野草 n.衣服；丧服 vi.除草；清除；淘汰', '1. The garden is choked with weeds. 花园杂草丛生。 2. She knelt down to pull a weed from the flower bed. 她跪下来拔除花圃上的杂草。 3. There are so many weeds in his field! 他的田里有那么多野草！ 4. He pulled off his coat and started to weed with us. 他脱去上装，开始和我们一起除草。', '过去式: weeded 过去分词: weeded 现在分词: weeding 第三人称单数: weeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flower', '[\'flaʊər]', 'n.花；开花植物；精华；盛时 v.开花；成熟；用花装饰', '1. She picked up a pink flower from a foxglove. 她从毛地黄上摘了一朵粉花。 2. I dare not touch the flower for its tenderness. 这花太娇嫩了，我不敢碰它。 3. The plant has a brilliant purple flower. 那棵植物开著一朵鲜艳的紫花。 4. The flower languished from lack of water. 花因缺水而枯萎。 5. Cherry trees flower in the early spring. 樱桃树在早春开花。', '形容词: flowerless 名词: flowerer 过去式: flowered 过去分词: flowered 现在分词: flowering 第三人称单数: flowers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('erosion', '[ɪ\'rəʊʒn]', 'n.腐蚀；侵蚀；减少，流失', '1. Therefore, the corrosion was caused by erosion of rainwater during ocean shipping. 因此，这些腐蚀是海运途中雨水的浸蚀造成的。 2. The erosion of beach here is serious. 这里海岸的腐蚀很严重。 3. The cement petrified after many years\' erosion. 经过多年的侵蚀，水泥石化了。 4. The erosion of the soil is damaging the forest. 土壤侵蚀使得森林遭到了破坏。', '形容词: erosional 副词: erosionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('restrict', '[rɪ\'strɪkt]', 'vt.限制；约束', '1. In a move to restrict imports, the government raised custom duties. 政府在限制进口的措施中提高了关税。 2. Recent laws have tended to restrict the freedom of the press. 新法例有限制新闻自由的趋势。 3. I restrict myself to smoking two cigarettes a day. 我限定自己每天只抽两支烟。 4. Fog restricted visibility. 雾天能见度很低。', '名词: restrictor 过去式: restricted 过去分词: restricted 现在分词: restricting 第三人称单数: restricts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sum', '[sʌm]', 'n.金额；总数；要点 v.概括；总结；归纳；总计', '1. I had to spend a large sum of money to get it back. 我得花一大笔钱才把它弄回来。 2. I save a nice little sum out of my wages each week. 我从每周的工资中节省一笔可观的金额。 3. The sum of 5 and 3 is 8. 五加三的总和是八。 4. Is that the sum of what you\'ve done in the last two years? 这就是你最近两年中完成的全部数量吗？ 5. We can sum up the main point of the lesson in three sentences. 我们可以用三句话来概括本课要点。', '过去式: summed 过去分词: summed 现在分词: summing 第三人称单数: sums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ignorant', '[\'ɪɡnərənt]', 'adj.无知的；愚昧的；不知道的', '1. He\'s so ignorant that he cannot write his own name. 他很无知，连自己的名字都写不出。 2. She regarded her critics as ignorant and prejudiced. 她认为那些批评她的人既无知又存有偏见。 3. Ignorant children sometimes laugh at beggars and tramps. 无知的孩子们有时会嘲笑乞丐和无家可归的人。 4. His ignorant behaviour at the dinner table caused much embarrassment. 他在餐桌上举止粗鲁，在座的人颇为难堪。', '副词: ignorantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cordial', '[\'kɔːrdʒəl]', 'n.兴奋剂；补品 adj.热忱的；诚恳的；兴奋的', '1. By means of a few drops of strong cordial, the doctor revived the besotted corpse for a few minutes. 博士滴了几滴强烈的兴奋剂，使这个没有知觉的身躯复活了几分钟。 2. It was a cordial affair in which Pancalli expressed his appreciation for the work carried out by Juventus in recent months. 这是一次热忱的会晤，潘卡利感谢了近几个月来尤文所做的工作。 3. Please accept my cordial and humblest apologies. 请接受我诚恳的道歉。', '副词: cordially 名词: cordiality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wrong', '[rɔːŋ]', 'adj.错误的；有毛病的；不适当的；不道德的 adv.错误地 n.不义行为；坏事；犯罪；欺骗；错误；不公正 v.冤枉；不公正地对待', '1. I am afraid you\'ve made a wrong decision. 恐怕你做了一个错误的决定。 2. I\'m not going to bow down to such wrong opinions. 我不打算听从这种错误的意见。 3. There is something wrong with the car. 这车有点毛病。 4. What\'s wrong with the engine? It\'s making an awful noise. 发动机出什麽故障了? 噪音太大了. 5. You\'ve spelt the word wrong. 你把这个单词拼错了。 6. Children must be taught the difference right and wrong. 必须教儿童分清是非。 7. You wronged him by saying that he had lied. 你说他说谎是冤枉了他。', '副词: wrongly 名词: wronger 过去式: wronged 过去分词: wronged 现在分词: wronging 第三人称单数: wrongs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stripe', '[straɪp]', 'n.条纹；条纹布；种类；军士军阶 n.鞭打；抽打 vt.使 ... 带有条纹', '1. I need one without stripe, please. 我需要没有条纹的。 2. The entire body of a zebra is marked with black and whitish stripe. 斑马的全身都有黑白条纹。 3. Which do you want for your new dress, a stripe or a check? 你要哪种料子来做新连衣裙，条子的还是方格的? 4. \"All Fascists are not of one mind, one stripe\" (Lillian Hellman) 所有的法西斯主义者并非一个思想,一个种类。', '过去式: striped 过去分词: striped 现在分词: striping 第三人称单数: stripes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ago', '[ə\'ɡoʊ]', 'adv.以前', '1. The dinosaurs disappeared long ago. 恐龙很久以前就绝种了。 2. A hundred years ago, Britain had a large empire. 一百年以前，英国有一个很大的帝国。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('continual', '[kən\'tɪnjuəl]', 'adj.不断的；频繁的；连续的', '1. Are you tired of this continual rain? 你对于这不停的雨不感到厌烦吗？ 2. The child\'s continual crying drove me to distraction. 那孩子不断的哭声弄得我几乎要发狂。 3. The noise of cars passing along the road is a continual disturbance to our quiet at home. 马路上来往的车辆声音不断地破坏我们家的安宁。 4. My work has been delayed by his continual visit. 我的工作被他频繁的拜访给耽搁了。', '副词: continually');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('his', '[hɪz]', 'adj.他的 pron.他的', '1. Next Tuesday is his birthday. 下周二是他的生日。 2. He claims it was his idea. 他声称这是他的主意。 3. His brother is my classmate. 他哥哥是我的同学。 4. His name leapt out at me from the newspaper. 报纸上他的名字一下子跳入我的眼帘。 5. This book is his, not yours. 这本书是他的，不是你的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alike', '[ə\'laɪk]', 'adj.相似的；同样的 adv.一样；以同样的方式', '1. We are much alike in character. 我们的性格很相似。 2. The two brothers are very much alike. 这两兄弟非常相像。 3. The sisters are as alike as two peas. 两姐妹长得一模一样。 4. These kittens look exactly alike how can you tell which is which? 这些小猫看上去一模一样--你怎么能分出哪个是哪个? 5. No two people think alike. 没有两个人的想法是一样的。', '名词: alikeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('withstand', '[wɪð\'stænd]', 'vt.对抗；经得起；承受', '1. He slew all who dared to withstand him. 他把敢于对抗他的人都斩尽杀绝。 2. Explorers have to withstand hardships. 探险者得忍受艰苦。 3. They could not withstand the fierceness of attack of those soldiers. 他们抵挡不住那些士兵猛烈的进攻。 4. This dress material will withstand repeated washing. 这种衣料经得住反复洗涤。', '名词: withstander 过去式: withstood 过去分词: withstood 现在分词: withstanding 第三人称单数: withstands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('teach', '[tiːtʃ]', 'vt.教；教导；教授；教训 vi.给予指导', '1. I taught her to ride a bicycle. 我教她骑自行车。 2. His parents employed a tutor to teach him Greek. 他父母雇佣了一位家庭教师来教他希腊语。 3. Parents should teach their children table manners. 双亲应该教导他们的小孩餐桌礼仪。 4. I\'ve been invited to teach Chinese at the University of New York for one year. 我应聘去纽约大学讲授一年汉语。 5. I am going to teach until my son can earn money. 我教书要教到我儿子能够赚钱。', '过去式: taught 过去分词: taught 现在分词: teaching 第三人称单数: teaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resolution', '[ˌrezə\'luːʃn]', 'n.决心；决定；解决；决议；坚决；分辨率', '1. Nothing can unsettle his resolution. 什么也动摇不了他的决心。 2. Making resolution on new year\'s day is a custom that still prevail. 在新年这一天下决心是一个依然流行的习俗。 3. The committee have adopted a resolution to build a park. 委员会做出一个项决议，决定兴建一座公园。 4. His generosity led to the resolution of all our difficulties. 他的慷慨相助使我们的困难全都得以解决。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('council', '[\'kaʊnsl]', 'n.地方议会；委员会；理事会；会议；委员', '1. She\'s on the local council. 她是地方议会的议员。 2. The theatre is under the patronage of the Arts Council. 那家剧院得到了艺术委员会的赞助。 3. Three women have been elected to the Council. 有3名妇女当选为市政委员会委员。 4. We should submit our plans to the council for approval. 我们应该向理事会提交计划以求批准。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mount', '[maʊnt]', 'v.登上；爬上；装上；上升 n.底板；爬上；支架；乘用马 n.山；峰', '1. He mounted the horse and rode off. 他骑上马走了。 2. Be careful not to mount the pavement when you\'re parking the car. 你停车时,小心不要停上人行道。 3. The frame on desk can make independent shelf already, also can conveniently mount. 书桌上的架子既能成为独立的书架,也能方便地装上。 4. His debts continued to mount up. 他的债务在不断增长。 5. The general had an excellent mount. 将军有出色的坐骑。 6. Mount Jolmo Lungma is the highest mountain in the world. 珠穆朗玛峰是世界上最高的山峰。', '形容词: mountable 名词: mounter 过去式: mounted 过去分词: mounted 现在分词: mounting 第三人称单数: mounts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('result', '[rɪ\'zʌlt]', 'n.结果；成果；答案；成绩；(足球比赛)赢 v.产生；致使', '1. These problems are the result of years of bad management. 这些问题是由于多年管理不善而造成的。 2. The presumable result is an election defeat. 推测结果是竞选可能会失败。 3. She looked with pride at the result of her work. 她自豪地看着自己的工作成果. 4. If you cube 10, the result is 1000. 十自乘两次,结果为一千。 5. If law and order break down, anarchy will result. 法治一垮，就会出现无政府状态。', '形容词: resultful 名词: resultfulness 过去式: resulted 过去分词: resulted 现在分词: resulting 第三人称单数: results');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('innumerable', '[ɪ\'nuːmərəbl]', 'adj.无数的；数不清的', '1. Human beings once created innumerable miracles. 人类曾经创造了无数的奇迹。 2. Stars resemble innumerable dots of lights in the night sky. 夜空中，星星象无数的小亮点。 3. There are innumerable constellations in the sky. 天空中有数不清的星座。 4. Innumerable small shops presented a collection of cheap plastic goods. 数不清的小商店里陈列着一批廉价的塑料制品。', '副词: innumerably 名词: innumerableness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('explode', '[ɪk\'sploʊd]', 'vi.爆炸；激增；爆发 vt.使爆炸；驳倒', '1. The bomb was timed to explode during the rush-hour. 炸弹选在人最多时爆炸。 2. When the boiler exploded many people were injured. 因锅炉爆炸，许多人受了伤。 3. The firework exploded in his hand. 那个爆竹在他手里响了。 4. Investment in technology stocks exploded in the 1990s. 二十世纪九十年代的,对科技股票的投资迅速增加。 5. The children exploded three firecrackers. 孩子们燃放了三个爆竹', '名词: exploder 过去式: exploded 过去分词: exploded 现在分词: exploding 第三人称单数: explodes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wedding', '[\'wedɪŋ]', 'n.婚礼；结合', '1. We decided to delay our wedding until next year. 我们决定把婚礼推迟到明年。 2. She reproached her husband for having forgotten their wedding anniversary. 她责怪丈夫忘了他们的结婚周年纪念日。 3. The coalition government was obviously a shotgun wedding. 这个联合政府显然是勉强的结合。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('infinite', '[\'ɪnfɪnət]', 'adj.无穷的；无限的 n.无限', '1. The number of positive numbers is infinite. 正数的数目是无穷的。 2. Teaching little children takes infinite patience. 教幼儿需有极大的耐心。 3. It is difficult to grasp the concept of infinite space. 掌握无限空间的概念是很难的。 4. Incense can attune the finite to the Infinite. 薰香可以使有限调谐至无限。', '副词: infinitely 名词: infiniteness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('safety', '[\'seɪfti]', 'n.安全；保险', '1. The new car design incorporates all the latest safety features. 新的汽车设计具备最新安全措施的一切特点。 2. The safety of the ship is the captain\'s responsibility. 确保船只的安全是船长的责任。 3. The management took all reasonable safety precautions. 管理部门采取了一切合理的安全措施。 4. It\'s very important to teach the children about road safety. 把交通安全常识教给孩子们是非常重要的。', '名词复数: safeties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sophomore', '[\'sɑːfəmɔːr]', 'n.（北美）大学（或中学）二年级学生 adj.第二年的', '1. Lily is a Sophomore now. 莉莉现在大学二年级。 2. toolbox talk 工作前的安全会议 3. Henry is in his sophomore year. 亨利在读二年级。 4. My sophomore year of college was perhaps the most remarkable year of my life. 大二的生活也许是我生命中最值得留念的一段。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('farmer', '[\'fɑːrmər]', 'n.农夫；农民；农场主', '1. The farmer has a shepherd dog. 农夫有一条牧羊犬。 2. The farmer was pleased to see his piles of corns on the cob. 农夫很高兴地看着成堆的玉米。 3. A farmer must plow the land before planting crops. 农民在种庄稼前必须犁地。 4. The farmer paid 3 laborers to gather the crop. 农场主雇佣3名工人收割庄稼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unlikely', '[ʌn\'laɪkli]', 'adj.不太可能的', '1. The superpowers are unlikely to disarm completely. 超级大国不太可能彻底裁军。 2. But a spending bonanza is unlikely. 但是，应有尽有也不太可能。', '比较级: unlikelier 最高级: unlikeliest 名词: unlikeliness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('afford', '[ə\'fɔːrd]', 'v.花费得起；能够做；承担得起(后果)；提供；给予', '1. Only the well-to-do can afford these houses. 只有富人能买得起这些房子。 2. I can\'t afford a holiday this summer. 今年夏天我无法度假。 3. We can afford to overlook minor offences. 我们可以不计较小过。 4. We can\'t afford to pay such a price. 我们付不起这个价钱。', '过去式: afforded 过去分词: afforded 现在分词: affording 第三人称单数: affords');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bald', '[bɔːld]', 'adj.秃头的；单调的；无装饰的 v.（使）变秃头', '1. He shaved his head bald. 他剃了个光头。 2. He has a shiny bald pate. 他是个亮光光的秃顶。 3. We planted some trees on the bald hill. 我们在一座秃山上种了些树。 4. He took off the hat and revealed his bald head. 他脱下帽子，露出秃头。 5. I am starting to bald noticeably. 我头顶明显地开始变秃了。', '副词: baldly 比较级: balder 最高级: baldest 名词: baldness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cushion', '[\'kʊʃn]', 'n.垫子；橡皮软垫；缓冲 vt.加垫褥；放在垫子上；保护；减缓；为 ... 装垫子', '1. He covered the cushion with new material. 他给靠垫蒙上了新的料子。 2. She embroidered the cushion with flowers. 她把垫子绣上了花。 3. A hovercraft rides on a cushion of air. 气垫船悬浮在气垫上行驶. 4. The bush acted as a cushion to my fall. 这灌木在我摔下时起了缓冲作用。 5. We are going to cushion the rocking chair so that it is more comfortable. 我们要在摇椅上铺软垫，那么就会更舒适了。', '形容词: cushiony 过去式: cushioned 过去分词: cushioned 现在分词: cushioning 第三人称单数: cushions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('campaign', '[kæm\'peɪn]', 'n.运动；战役；活动；竞选运动 v.参加竞选；从事运动', '1. The campaign was a blockbuster. 这次竞选运动声势浩大。 2. They are planning a new campaign against corruption. 他们正在策划一个新的反贪污运动。 3. The campaign to seize the city was a failure. 攻占这个城市的战役失败了。 4. We were outmanoeuvred and outfought throughout the winter campaign. 我们在整个冬季战役中始终不如对手。 5. He announced that he would campaign for the senate. 他宣布他将参加议员竞选。', '名词: campaigner 过去式: campaigned 过去分词: campaigned 现在分词: campaigning 第三人称单数: campaigns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('individual', '[ˌɪndɪ\'vɪdʒuəl]', 'adj.单独的；一个人的；独有的 n.个人；个体', '1. A teacher can\'t give individual attention to each pupil if his class is large. 如果班上的人数多，老师就不能给予个别辅导了。 2. It is difficult for a teacher to give individual attention to children in a large class. 教师在人数多的班上，很难对各个学生都照顾到。 3. She has her own individual style of doing things. 她有自己独特的行事风格。 4. No individual shall overtop the law. 任何个人的权力都不能凌驾于法律之上。', '副词: individually');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('traitor', '[\'treɪtər]', 'n.叛徒；卖国贼；出卖朋友者', '1. The infamous traitor was sentenced to death. 那个罪大恶极的叛徒被判处死刑。 2. He struck a knife into the traitor\'s heart. 他将刀戳入卖国贼的心脏。 3. The traitor sold our important military secrets to the enemy. 这卖国贼把我方重要的军事秘密卖给敌人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('race', '[reɪs]', 'n.赛跑；竞争 n.人种；种族；血统 v.赛跑；竞赛', '1. Every morning he spent two hours training for the race. 他每天早晨花两个小时练习赛跑。 2. We are all involved in a rat race, whether we want to be or not. 不管我们愿不愿意,我们都进行着激烈的竞争。 3. The Chinese belong to the yellow race. 中国人属于黄种人。 4. He is against race prejudice. 他反对种族歧视。 5. I\'ll race you to the bus stop. 我要和你赛一赛，看谁先跑到汽车站。', '过去式: raced 过去分词: raced 现在分词: racing 第三人称单数: races');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('repel', '[rɪ\'pel]', 'vt.排斥；抵制；击退；使反感 vi.排斥；反感', '1. The positive poles of two magnets repel each other. 两块磁铁的正极互相排斥。 2. They stood prepared to repel any attack. 他们准备好打退一切进攻。 3. The crew repelled the attack. 船员击退了进攻。 4. A country must have the will to repel any invader. 一个国家得有决心击退任何入侵者。 5. The positive poles of two magnets repel each other. 两块磁铁的正极互相排斥。', '名词: repeller 过去式: repelled 过去分词: repelled 现在分词: repelling 第三人称单数: repels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crush', '[krʌʃ]', 'v.压碎；击败；使...失望；折皱；压榨 n.压碎；压榨；极度拥挤；<口>迷恋', '1. A windmill is used to crush grain into flour. 风车被用来把谷粒轧成面粉。 2. It took him only 50 minutes to crush his opponent. 他只用了50分钟时间就击败了对手。 3. This victory inspired vigor in the Armenian national team and they finally crushed the English team. 这场胜利激起了亚美尼亚队的斗志,他们最终击败了英国队。 4. I was crushed that I wasn\'t invited. 没有受到邀请,我感到很失望。 5. I\'ve got a crush on my pretty toy pistol. 我非常喜欢我漂亮的玩具手枪。', '形容词: crushable 名词: crusher 过去式: crushed 过去分词: crushed 现在分词: crushing 第三人称单数: crushes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('old', '[oʊld]', 'adj.老的；过去的；旧的，破旧的；... 岁的 n.旧时', '1. The old lady fondled her cat as it sat beside her. 老妇人抚摸着蹲在身边的小猫。 2. He invited me to his home to talk over old times. 他邀我到他家里去聊聊过去的事。 3. The cupboard was stuffed with old fishing tackle. 小橱里塞满了旧的钓鱼用具。 4. Public opinion was against the old feudal system. 公众舆论反对旧的封建制度。', '比较级: older 最高级: oldest 名词: oldness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relationship', '[rɪ\'leɪʃnʃɪp]', 'n.关系；联系；亲属关系', '1. Part of my job is to maintain good relationship with our suppliers. 我的部分工作是同我们的供应商保持良好的关系。 2. We have a working relationship. 我们是工作上的关系。 3. I\'m not going to give my son the job just because of our relationship. 我不打算把这个职位给我的儿子,正因为我们有这层亲属关系。 4. Is there any relationship between them? 它们之间有联系吗?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('somewhat', '[\'sʌmwʌt]', 'adv.稍微；有些；多少；几分 pron.某物；一些', '1. Their swimming pool is somewhat deep than ours. 他们的游泳池比我们的游泳池稍微深一点儿。 2. The price was somewhat higher than I\'d expected. 这价格比我预料的稍高一些。 3. We are suffering somewhat from the heat. 我们因为酷热有些不好受。 4. His explanation overreached somewhat. 他的辩解多少有点过火。 5. The exact program of research we pursue will be somewhat driven by the people that we\'re able to attract. 精确的计画研究我们追求将会是被我们能够吸引的人驱使的某物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('winter', '[\'wɪntər]', 'n.冬季；冬天 adj.冬天的；冬季生长的 vi.过冬 vt.对 ... 进行过冬保护', '1. Winter is the coldest season in a year. 冬季是一年中最冷的季节。 2. Winter is the low season at seaside hotels. 冬季是海滨旅馆业的淡季。 3. Every winter some old people die from hypothermia. 每年冬天都有些老人死于体温过低。 4. The bears den up together during the winter. 冬天熊一起在洞穴里冬眠。 5. The severeness of the winter made her weaker. 冬天的严酷使她身体更加虚弱。 6. They have stored up much fuel for the winter. 他们已储存大量过冬用的燃料。', '形容词: winterish 过去式: wintered 过去分词: wintered 现在分词: wintering 第三人称单数: winters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deduct', '[dɪ\'dʌkt]', 'vt.扣除；演绎', '1. Nowadays income tax is normally deducted from a person\'s wages. 现在，所得税通常是在发工资前就已经扣除了。 2. Tax is deducted from your salary. 税金从你的薪金中扣除。 3. You may deduct your families health insurance. 你可以扣除你的家庭健康保险. 4. It is not the bank\'s policy to deduct interest on withdrawal. 提款需扣除利息这并非是本银行的政策。', '过去式: deducted 过去分词: deducted 现在分词: deducting 第三人称单数: deducts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inner', '[\'ɪnər]', 'adj.内心的；内部的；里面的 n.里面', '1. He has no inner resources and hates being alone. 他没有内在的精神寄托，因而害怕孤独。 2. Her artificial gaiety disguised an inner sadness. 她以矫揉造作的快乐掩饰著内心的悲痛。 3. I no longer felt the inner restraint. 我再也不感到内心的压抑了。 4. Does it ever occur to you to use your sight to see into the inner nature of a friend or acquaintance? 你曾否想到用你的视觉去探视一位朋友或认识的人的内在本性？ 5. Time is therefore always ticking in our inner ear. 因此时间总是在我们内耳里面滴滴答答地走。', '副词: innerly 名词: innerness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('originate', '[ə\'rɪdʒɪneɪt]', 'v.发起；开始；起源于；[计算机] 起始', '1. They originated the plan. 他们首先提出这一计划。 2. Who originated the concept of stereo sound? 立体声是谁发明的？ 3. And how did this peculiar custom originate? 而且，这种奇特的习俗又是怎么开始的呢? 4. The quarrel originated in rivalry between the two families. 这次争吵是两家不和引起的。', '形容词: originative 副词: originatively 名词: origination 过去式: originated 过去分词: originated 现在分词: originating 第三人称单数: originates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sprout', '[spraʊt]', 'v.长芽；萌芽；迅速成长 n.芽；年幼者', '1. The seeds will sprout in a few days. 这些种子几天后就会发芽。 2. These potatoes have begun to sprout. 这些马铃薯开始发芽了。 3. The seeds sprout into small, hairlike seedings. 种子发育成小小的、毛茸茸的幼苗。 4. He sprouted up six inches a year. 他一年长高了六英寸。 5. In spring, here, drizzle moistens land , also feed rice sprout. 春天，这里细雨蒙蒙，滋润着土地，也哺育着稻苗。', '过去式: sprouted 过去分词: sprouted 现在分词: sprouting 第三人称单数: sprouts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('complain', '[kəm\'pleɪn]', 'vi.抱怨；控诉；诉说', '1. The tourist complained that the room was too dirty. 游客抱怨说房间太脏了。 2. She complained to me about his rudeness. 他向我抱怨他的卤莽。 3. He will complain to the police that I struck him. 这人要到警察局去控告我打他。 4. The patient is complaining of acute earache. 病人说耳部剧痛。', '名词: complainer 过去式: complained 过去分词: complained 现在分词: complaining 第三人称单数: complains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('parameter', '[pə\'ræmɪtər]', 'n.参量；参数；决定因素；界限', '1. One parameter which always comes into play is the national economy. 国民经济是一个经常起作用的参量。 2. Spend by each department have to fall within certain parameter. 每个部门的开支必须属于确定的系数之内。 3. You can pass report parameters to a DMX query parameter. 您可以将报表参数传递到DMX查询参数。 4. A notable question is whether there is parameter in it. 一个值得注意的问题是是否有限定因素.', '形容词: parametric 副词: parametrically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sustain', '[sə\'steɪn]', 'vt.支持；承受；维持；认可；经受', '1. His hope for future sustained him. 对未来的希望支持了他。 2. The ice will not sustain your weight. 这冰承受不了你的体重。 3. Some species may not be able to sustain the pressure from such prevalent raids. 一些物种无法承受这种猖撅的偷猎行为带来的压力。 4. They had sufficient food to sustain life. 他们有足够维持生命的食物。', '形容词: sustainable 名词: sustainability 过去式: sustained 过去分词: sustained 现在分词: sustaining 第三人称单数: sustains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('equipment', '[ɪ\'kwɪpmənt]', 'n.设备；装备；器材', '1. The government has an interest in importing scientific equipment. 政府对引进科学设备非常感兴趣。 2. We should make a better use of the existing equipment. 我们应该更好地利用现有设备。 3. The equipment must be bought from a supplier approved by the company. 设备必须从公司认可的供应商那里购买。 4. The Army is auctioning off a lot of old equipment. 军队正在把大量旧装备拍卖掉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('structure', '[\'strʌktʃər]', 'n.结构；构造；建筑物 vt.构造；建造；组织', '1. Can you analyze the structure of the sentence for me? 你能给我分析一下这个句子的结构吗？ 2. Most linguists would say they were concerned primarily with the structure of languages. 大多数语言学家都会说，他们主要研究各种语言的结构。 3. We learnt about the structure of the brain today. 今天我们学习了大脑的构造。 4. The structure had keeled over in the high winds. 那座建筑物让大风给刮倒了。 5. We learnt about the structure of the brain today. 今天我们学习了大脑的构造。', '过去式: structured 过去分词: structured 现在分词: structuring 第三人称单数: structures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('craft', '[kræft]', 'n.工艺；手艺；狡诈；船舶；航空器；行会成员 vt.手工制作；精心制作', '1. He graduated from a school of crafts and arts. 他毕业于一所工艺美术学校。 2. He learned his craft from an old master. 他从一位老匠人那儿学得他的手艺。 3. By crafts the gambler tricked them out of all their money. 那个赌徒用诡计赢去了他们所有的钱。 4. Hundreds of small craft accompany the liner into harbour. 数百只小艇随同这艘班轮驶入港湾。 5. He told us a carefully crafted story. 他给我们讲了一个精心编织的故事。', '名词: crafter 过去式: crafted 过去分词: crafted 现在分词: crafting 第三人称单数: crafts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('story', '[\'stɔːri]', 'n.故事；传说；谎言；叙述；新闻报道；情节 n.楼层(=storey) v.以历史事件为图案装饰', '1. The story stirred her sympathy. 这故事激起了她的同情心。 2. The story took place in a serene summer night. 故事发生在一个宁静的夏夜。 3. This novel has been developed out of a folk story. 这部小说脱胎于民间传说。 4. He took the girl in with his stories. 他用一套谎言蒙骗了那个女孩。 5. That is a house of six stories. 那是一栋六层楼的房子。', '名词复数: stories 过去式: storied 过去分词: storied 现在分词: storying 第三人称单数: stories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('circumference', '[sər\'kʌmfərəns]', 'n.圆周；周围；周长', '1. That point falls on the circumference of the circle. 那一个点落在这圆的圆周线上。 2. He went jogging around the circumference of the reservoir every morning. 他每天早晨绕着水库周围慢跑。 3. This tree has a circumference of 6 feet. 这棵树周长六英尺。 4. The circumference of the earth is almost 25,000 miles. 地球的圆周长约为两万五千英里。', '形容词: circumferential');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('horsepower', '[\'hɔːrspaʊər]', 'n.马力(功率单位)', '1. The horsepower of the engine is very low. 该发动机的马力很小。 2. I\'ll need a bit more horsepower to get up this hill. 我需要更大的马力来登上这座山。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forget', '[fər\'ɡet]', 'v.忘记；忽略', '1. I\'m sorry; I\'ve forgotten your name. 对不起，我忘了你的名字。 2. I almost forget to pay the phone bill. 我几乎忘记电话费用。 3. We must not forget about the grass roots. 我们绝不能忘记民众。 4. That was a moment that I shall never forget. 那个时刻我永远不会忘记。', '名词: forgetter 过去式: forgot 过去分词: forgotten/forgot 现在分词: forgetting 第三人称单数: forgets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clarity', '[\'klærəti]', 'n.清楚；透明', '1. These adjectives mean lacking clarity of meaning. 这些形容词都有意思不清楚的含义。 2. Let me try to provide some clarity. 让我提供一些清楚的信息。 3. Clarity is very important for a business letter. 文笔清晰对于商业信件非常重要。 4. Clarity of dictionis vital for a public speaker. 发音清晰对演说家至关重要。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lens', '[lenz]', 'n.镜头；镜片；透镜；(眼球的)水晶体 v.给…摄影；给…拍照', '1. Don\'t smear the lens; I\'ve just polished it. 别把镜头弄脏了，我刚刚擦过。 2. Some adjustment of the lens may be necessary. 可能有必要调节一下镜头。 3. The camera lens must be screened from direct sunlight. 照相机的镜头不可受到阳光的直射。 4. He uses lens to make things appear clearer. 他用镜片以便看东西更清楚些。', '形容词: lensed 名词复数: lenses 过去式: lensed 过去分词: lensed 现在分词: lensing 第三人称单数: lenses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('warm', '[wɔːrm]', 'adj.温暖的；暖和的；热情的 v.变暖；使暖和 n.温暖的空气', '1. It\'s a nice and warm today. 今天的天气晴朗而且温暖。 2. Take your coat off. It\'s warm in the room. 把外衣脱掉,室内很暖和。 3. He was pleased with their warm welcome. 他们的热烈欢迎使他很高兴。 4. The weather has warmed up. 天气转暖了。 5. Come out of the cold street into the warm. 街上寒冷，进来暖和暖和。', '形容词: warmish 副词: warmly 比较级: warmer 最高级: warmest 名词: warmer 过去式: warmed 过去分词: warmed 现在分词: warming 第三人称单数: warms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dusk', '[dʌsk]', 'n.黄昏；薄暮；幽暗', '1. The lights go on at dusk. 一到黄昏灯就亮了。 2. He usually goes out for a walk at dusk. 他通常在黄昏时出去散步。 3. He works from dawn till dusk. 他从天亮工作到天黑。 4. We made a landfall at dusk after three weeks at sea. 在海上航行三周后的一个黄昏,我们看到了陆地。', '过去式: dusked 过去分词: dusked 现在分词: dusking 第三人称单数: dusks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drop', '[drɑːp]', 'vt.落下；跌倒；下降；放弃；漏掉；断绝关系 n.滴；微量；减少；滴状物', '1. She dropped to safety from the burning building. 她从失火的建筑物上坠落到安全的地方. 2. He dropped off from his bike. 他从自行车上跌下来。 3. In the winter the temperature often drops below freezing. 冬天的时候,温度往往会降到冰点以下。 4. I decided to drop chemistry and take biology instead. 我决定放弃化学,改学生物。 5. Unconsciously, a drop of tear drips on his lips. 不知不觉,一滴泪水滴在他唇上。', '过去式: dropped 过去分词: dropped 现在分词: dropping 第三人称单数: drops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eat', '[iːt]', 'v.吃；吃饭；喝', '1. I often eat oatmeal as breakfast. 我经常吃燕麦粥当早饭。 2. Do you always eat lunch at school? 你总是在学校吃午饭吗？ 3. If you eat too much chocolate you\'ll get fat. 吃巧克力太多会发胖。 4. The Chinese eat with chopsticks. 中国人用筷子吃饭。', '名词: eater 过去式: ate 过去分词: eaten 现在分词: eating 第三人称单数: eats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dessert', '[dɪ\'zɜːrt]', 'n.甜食，餐后甜点', '1. I like to have ice cream for dessert. 我喜欢在正餐后吃冰淇淋当甜点。 2. Can I have some fruit instead of the dessert? 可不可以不要甜点改要水果？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nature', '[\'neɪtʃər]', 'n.自然界；性质；自然；自然状态；本性；类型', '1. In fact, nature is much better at recycling than we humans are. 事实上,自然界在再循环方面比人类做得更好。 2. To a great extent, that is the nature of my own work. 在很大程度上,这就是我工作的性质。 3. The goal of life is living in agreement with nature. 人生的终极目标是和自然和谐相处。 4. Why is the state of nature a state of war? 为何自然状态是一种战争的状态？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('afraid', '[ə\'freɪd]', 'adj.抱歉的；担心的；害怕的', '1. I\'m afraid we can\'t come. 很抱歉，我们不能来。 2. I\'m afraid I didn\'t quie catch what you said. 对不起,我没听清你刚才所说的话。 3. I didn\'t mention it because I was afraid of upsetting him/afraid (that) I might upset him. 我没有提起那件事，因为我怕他心烦意乱。 4. Are you afraid of snakes? 你怕蛇吗?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('confess', '[kən\'fes]', 'v.承认；供认；告解；听取忏悔', '1. I confess you are right on one point. 我承认你在某一点上是正确的。 2. Now, I must confess that I\'m at my wit\'s end. 现在我必须承认我已毫无办法。 3. He confessed that he had never seen her before. 他承认以前从未见过她。 4. He refused to confess to his crime. 他拒绝认罪。', '形容词: confessable 副词: confessedly 过去式: confessed 过去分词: confessed 现在分词: confessing 第三人称单数: confesses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('organ', '[\'ɔːrɡən]', 'n.器官；风琴；机构；喉舌；报刊', '1. The heart is a vital organ. 心脏是维持生命必须的器官。 2. The old organ wheezed out a tune. 那架老风琴呜呜地奏出曲子。 3. The organ played as the bride came down the aisle. 当新娘沿着通道走过来时，风琴演奏了起来。 4. Parliament is an organ of government. 议会是政府的一个机构。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('something', '[\'sʌmθɪŋ]', 'pron.某事物；有价值或重要的人或事物；大致；左右 adv.有点；非常', '1. I think I dropped something. 我想我掉了东西。 2. I\'ll try and rustle you up something to eat. 我设法给你弄点吃的。 3. I can predict something with great accuracy. 我能很准确地预测某事。 4. He thinks he\'s something. 他认为他了不起。 5. He is something like his brother. 他有点象他哥哥。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lady', '[\'leɪdi]', 'n.夫人；女士', '1. The lady looked at me with a contented smile. 那位夫人带着满意的微笑看着我。 2. The lady assured to him her daughter. 夫人把女儿许配给他。 3. The antique table went to the lady in the pink hat. 这张古董桌子卖给那位戴粉红色帽子的女士了。 4. He handed the old lady out of the cab. 他将这位上了年纪的女士从车上扶下来。', '名词复数: ladies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('foundation', '[faʊn\'deɪʃn]', 'n.根基；基础；根据；创建；基金(会)', '1. How long will it take to finish digging the foundations? 挖地基大概需要多长时间完成呢？ 2. He laid the foundation of his success by study and hard work. 他通过学习和努力工作为成功打下了基础。 3. All these have laid a solid political foundation for consolidated national unity. 所有这些为巩固国家统一奠定了坚实的政治基础。 4. His view is by no means without foundation. 他这种看法决不是凭空产生的。', '形容词: foundational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('noodle', '[\'nuːdl]', 'n.面条', '1. The noodle is in the shape of a waistbelt. 面条像腰带。 2. Please put more minced meat into my noodle soup. 请给我的面条里多加些肉末。', '过去式: noodled 过去分词: noodled 现在分词: noodling 第三人称单数: noodles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deposit', '[dɪ\'pɑːzɪt]', 'v.放置；(使)沉淀；存储；付(订金等)；寄存 n.存款；定金；堆积物；矿床', '1. She deposited a pile of books on my desk. 她把一摞书放在我的书桌上。 2. Coarse crumb rubber is apt to deposit in asphalt. 粗的橡胶颗粒容易在沥青中沉淀。 3. The Nile floods the fields and deposits mud on them. 尼罗河泛滥，在田野上淤积一层泥。 4. He deposits a sum of money in the bank each month. 他每月在银行存一笔钱。 5. Ten yuan is the minimum initial deposit. 最低的开户存款金额是十元。', '名词: depositor 过去式: deposited 过去分词: deposited 现在分词: depositing 第三人称单数: deposits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dot', '[dɑːt]', 'n.少量；小圆点；小东西 v.点缀；作小点记号 [计算机] 点.', '1. We are all fellow passengers on a dot of earth. 我们都是一小块土地上的过客。 2. The ship became a mere dot on the horizon. 船在远处的水平线上成了一个小点。 3. On the map towns were marked by a red dot. 在地图上，城镇是用小红点标出的。 4. The lake was dotted with little boats. 湖面上布满了小船。', '形容词: dotal 名词: dotter 过去式: dotted 过去分词: dotted 现在分词: dotting 第三人称单数: dots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('question', '[\'kwestʃən]', 'n.问题；疑问 v.询问；怀疑', '1. He gave me no chance to reply to his question. 他没有给我回答他问题的机会。 2. That is a great international question of the day. 那是当代的一个重大国际问题。 3. Make a mark where you have a question. 在有疑问的地方做个记号。 4. There was some question as to his honesty. 关于他的诚实，还有些疑问。 5. The teacher will question us on verbs. 老师将问我们关于动词的知识。', '副词: questioningly 名词: questioner 过去式: questioned 过去分词: questioned 现在分词: questioning 第三人称单数: questions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outdoor', '[\'aʊtdɔːr]', 'adj.户外的；野外的；露天的；喜爱户外活动的', '1. Children like outdoor activities. 孩子们喜欢户外活动。 2. Outdoor sunlight is very good for the health. 户外的阳光对健康很有好处。 3. He used to lead an outdoor life. 他以前习惯过野外生活。 4. It is the world\'s oldest outdoor movie garden. 这是世界上历史最悠久的花园式露天电影院。', '异体字: out-of-door');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('therefore', '[\'ðerfɔːr]', 'adv.因此；所以', '1. He was the only candidate; therefore, he was elected. 他是唯一的候选人，因此，他当选了。 2. We do not have enough money. Therefore we can not afford to buy the new car. 我们的钱不够,因此买不成这辆新车。 3. I was ill, and therefore I could not come. 我病了,所以没能来。 4. He was very tired, and therefore he didn\'t give the market report. 他非常疲倦，所以没能作市场报告。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fabric', '[\'fæbrɪk]', 'n.结构；织物；构造', '1. The whole fabric of the society was changed by the war. 战争改变了整个社会结构。 2. The cost of repairing the fabric of the church was very high. 修理教堂结构的花费非常大。 3. This fabric has a tear in it. 这织物上有个破洞。 4. The fabric was displayed on a wired stand. 那种织物陈列在金属制的架子上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drawer', '[drɔːr]', 'n.抽屉；出票人；制图员；拖曳者 （复）drawers：内裤.', '1. He found the money secreted in a drawer. 他找到了藏在抽屉里的钱。 2. There is a pair of scissors in the bottom drawer. 最底下的抽屉里有把剪刀。 3. The drawer will write the check. 出票人将填写支票。 4. A drawer may specify himself on a cheque as the payee. 出票人可以在支票上记载自己为收款人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cruise', '[kruːz]', 'n.巡航；漫游； 游艇 v.慢速行驶；乘船游览；游弋；巡游', '1. These cruise ships can turn round in two days. 这些游船可用两天的时间装卸完毕。 2. It was a bit choppy on the cruise but I was all right once I found my sea legs. 在航游中有点风浪，但一旦我习惯于坐船旅行我就没什么问题了。 3. Airliners now cruise the ocean at great speed. 现在的班机以高速作越洋飞行。 4. He and his wife were planning to cruise. 他和他妻子准备乘船周游世界。', '过去式: cruised 过去分词: cruised 现在分词: cruising 第三人称单数: cruises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fitting', '[\'fɪtɪŋ]', 'adj.合适的；恰当的 n.试穿；配件；装配 动词fit的现在分词和动名词形式.', '1. A fitting end to the meal would be a glass of port. 餐后一杯波尔图葡萄酒是挺合适的。 2. It was, in fine, a fitting end to the story. 总之，这是故事很恰当的结尾。 3. He expressed his thoughts in clear and fitting language. 他用明白恰当的语言来表达他的思想。 4. The fitting-room is at the corner. 试衣间在拐角处。', '副词: fittingly 名词: fittingness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('low', '[loʊ]', 'adj.低的；少的；低落的；低声的；卑劣的；低等的 adv.低地；低声地；低下地；廉价地 n.低水平；低价；低谷 v.哞哞叫', '1. The price they quoted was very low. 他们报的价很低。 2. Shadows are longer when the sun is low in the sky. 太阳很低时，物体的影子就很长。 3. We must reorder these items because stock gets low. 我们必须再订购这些物品,因为库存越来越少了。 4. He\'d play the violin when he was in low spirits. 他情绪低落的时候就拉小提琴。 5. The sun hung low over the misted valley. 太阳低悬在薄雾笼罩的山谷之上。 6. The value of the pound has fallen to a new low against the dollar. 英镑兑换美元的比值已经跌倒新的低点。', '比较级: lower 最高级: lowest 名词: lowness 过去式: lowed 过去分词: lowed 现在分词: lowing 第三人称单数: lows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spectrum', '[\'spektrəm]', 'n.系列；幅度；范围；光谱；[科]频谱', '1. There\'s a wide spectrum of opinions on this problem. 对这个问题的说法众说纷纭，莫衷一是。 2. There are tense competition in the whole spectrum of the industry. 整个工业领域竞争很激烈。 3. The press has published a wide spectrum of books. 这个出版社出版了一系列范围广泛的书籍。 4. In the spectrum, distinct colours shade into each other. 在光谱中，截然不同的颜色相互融合起来。', '名词复数: spectra');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('safe', '[seɪf]', 'adj.安全的；安然无恙的；可靠的；谨慎的 n.保险箱', '1. There is no safe landing on that coast. 那一带海岸没有安全的登陆处。 2. It is not safe to drive like that, you must slow down. 那样开车是不安全的,你必须减速。 3. The rescuers brought the climbers back safe and sound. 救援人员把登山的人都安然无恙地救了回来。 4. The train is a safe means of transportation. 火车是一种安全可靠的交通工具。 5. All valuables should be kept in the safe. 所有贵重物品应存放在保险箱。', '副词: safely 比较级: safer 最高级: safest 名词: safeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rival', '[\'raɪvl]', 'n.竞争者；对手；同伴 adj.竞争的 v.竞争；与 ... 相匹敌', '1. He is hound out of his job by jealous rival. 他受到忌妒他的竞争者的算计而被迫离职。 2. The party leader has been supplanted by his rival. 那位政党领导已被他的对手取而代之了。 3. He was utterly unscrupulous in his competition with rival firms. 他与对立公司竞争完全不讲道德。 4. Ships can\'t rival aircraft for speed. 轮船在速度方面无法与飞机匹敌。', '过去式: rivaled/rivalled 过去分词: rivaled/rivalled 现在分词: rivaling/rivalling 第三人称单数: rivals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('athlete', '[\'æθliːt]', 'n.运动员', '1. The athlete is suffering from muscular strain. 这名运动员正受肌肉劳损之苦。 2. She will make a very good athlete. 她将来会成为一名很好的运动员。 3. The athlete has an electrifying burst of speed. 这名运动员具有惊人的爆发速度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grow', '[ɡroʊ]', 'v.增加；生长；变成；种植；逐渐开始', '1. How tall you\'ve grown! 你都长这麽高了! 2. Plants cannot grow well in the absence of water. 没有水,植物就不能茁壮地生长。 3. She is growing into a beautiful young woman. 她渐渐出落成美丽的姑娘。 4. This district used to grow cotton on a large scale. 这个地区过去大量种棉花。', '副词: growingly 名词: grower 过去式: grew 过去分词: grown 现在分词: growing 第三人称单数: grows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evening', '[\'iːvnɪŋ]', 'n.晚上；傍晚；晚会', '1. Could you come back home early this evening? 今天晚上你能早回家吗？ 2. I had a severe headache that evening. 那天晚上我头特别疼。 3. In the evening we went to see a film. 晚上我们去看了一场电影。 4. The evening sky flamed with red and orange. 傍晚天空的颜色是一片火红和橘黄相间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('go', '[ɡoʊ]', 'v.去；离开；变得；进行 n.去；尝试；精力；一举', '1. We\' ll go for a walk if you feel like it. 你愿意的话,咱们就去散散步。 2. I must be going. 我该走了。 3. A few days later, things started to go wrong. 几天后,事情开始变糟。 4. Everything went very smoothly. 一切进展顺利。 5. The boat rolled gently with the come and go of small waves. 小船随着细浪来回轻轻荡漾。', '名词复数: goes 过去式: went 过去分词: gone 现在分词: going 第三人称单数: goes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('migrate', '[\'maɪɡreɪt]', 'vi.迁移；迁徙；转移', '1. These workers migrate from country to country in search of work. 这些工人为寻找工作从一个国家迁移到另一个国家。 2. Some tribes migrate with their cattle in search of fresh grass. 有些部落为了寻找新鲜的牧草而带着他们的牲畜迁移。 3. In some developing countries more and more people migrate to urban area. 在某些发展中的国家，越来越多的人向市区迁移。 4. Large numbers of birds migrate south every winter. 每年冬季大量的鸟类迁徙南方。', '名词: migrator 过去式: migrated 过去分词: migrated 现在分词: migrating 第三人称单数: migrates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sleeve', '[sliːv]', 'n.套管；袖子', '1. If it is necessary to have the joints under water, they must be bedded into a box or sleeve which absolutely prevents water from penetrating in. 如果有必要在水下接头，就必须把它们安置于绝对不渗水的密封盒子或套管中。 2. A stranger plucked at my sleeve as I was leaving. 我刚要离去，一个陌生人拽我的袖子。 3. He rolled up his sleeves and got to work in the garden. 他卷起了袖子，在花园里干起活来。', '形容词: sleeveless 过去式: sleeved 过去分词: sleeved 现在分词: sleeving 第三人称单数: sleeves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('garbage', '[\'ɡɑːrbɪdʒ]', 'n.垃圾；废物；食物残渣', '1. Please put the garbage in the dustbin. 请把垃圾放在桶里。 2. She threw the leftovers in the garbage. 她把剩饭倒进垃圾桶。 3. The smell of the garbage overpowered me. 垃圾的臭味使我无法忍受。 4. You are a garbage! 你真是个废物！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tempt', '[tempt]', 'vt.诱惑；怂恿；引诱；吸引', '1. The warm weather tempted us into going for a swim. 暖和的天气诱使我们去游泳。 2. I ought not to have let you tempt me into asking you a rude question. 我本来就不应该让你怂恿我跟你提出一个无礼的问题。 3. Those advertisements try to tempt people into buying their products. 那些广告试图怂恿大家去购买其产品。 4. He was tempted into making a false step. 他被引诱做了一件傻事。', '形容词: temptable 名词: tempter 过去式: tempted 过去分词: tempted 现在分词: tempting 第三人称单数: tempts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rapid', '[\'ræpɪd]', 'adj.短时间发生的；急速的；迅速的；快的；险峻的 n.急流；湍滩', '1. Cats have rapid reflexes. 猫的反应很敏捷. 2. The pound\'s rapid appreciation is creating problems for exporters. 英镑急速升值给出口商造成困难。 3. The rapid spread of the disease is alarming the medical authorities. 这种疾病的迅速蔓延使医疗当局感到忧虑不安。 4. With the rapid economical development, China\'s position on the international stage is getting more and more important. 随着经济迅速发展，中国在国际舞台上的地位变得愈来愈重要了。 5. The first rapid we went through was the easiest. 我们经过的第一道急流是最简单的。', '副词: rapidly 比较级: rapider 最高级: rapidest 名词: rapidity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sly', '[slaɪ]', 'adj.狡猾的；会心的；淘气的；诡异的', '1. She\'s a sly puss. 她是个刁滑的姑娘。 2. The sly fox nimbly eluded the dogs. 那只狡猾的狐狸灵活地躲避开那群狗。 3. He cast a sly glance at his bridge partner. 他向桥牌搭档使了个会意的眼色。 4. The sly cat stole the meat while the cook\'s back was turned. 淘气的猫趁厨师转身之机偷吃了肉。', '副词: slyly 比较级: slier/slyer 最高级: sliest/slyest 名词: slyness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('personal', '[\'pɜːrsənl]', 'adj.私人的；个人的 n.(报刊)私人专栏', '1. I have something personal to discuss with you. 我有点私事和你商量。 2. I need your advice on a personal matter, but it\'s not about me. 有一件私事我想听听你的建议,但不是我的事。 3. It is my own, growing out of my personal concern. 是我自己提出的,完全出于我个人的关切。 4. Within two hours, I got my personal statement done. 仅花了两个小时,我就把个人陈述写好了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Christmas', '[\'krɪsməs]', 'n.圣诞节', '1. We usually sing carols at Christmas. 圣诞节时，我们一般会唱颂歌。 2. Christmas is a time of mirth, especially for children. 圣诞节是个快乐的日子，尤其是对孩子们。 3. They decorated the Christmas tree with tinsel. 他们用亮金属片装饰圣诞树。', '形容词: Christmassy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('vulnerable', '[\'vʌlnərəbl]', 'adj.易受伤害的；有弱点的；脆弱的', '1. Achilles was vulnerable only in his heel. 阿基里斯只有脚后跟会受伤害。 2. The potato is vulnerable to several pests. 马铃薯易受几种害虫的侵害。 3. Young birds are very vulnerable to predators. 幼小的鸟易受食肉动物伤害。 4. Satellites are as vulnerable as they are valuable. 卫星价值很大但也很脆弱。', '副词: vulnerably 名词: vulnerability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brain', '[breɪn]', 'n.脑；智力；智者；控制中心 vt.打 ... 的脑袋', '1. The drug may cause permanent brain damage. 这种药可能会引起永久性的脑部伤害。 2. His brain seems to be functioning normally. 他的大脑看起来功能正常。 3. His brain was clouded by vapours and dreams. 他的脑子里充满空想和梦幻。 4. She has a good brain. 她很有头脑。 5. I\'ll brain you if you don\'t keep quiet. 如果你不保持安静的话，我就敲你的脑袋。', '过去式: brained 过去分词: brained 现在分词: braining 第三人称单数: brains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('profitable', '[\'prɑːfɪtəbl]', 'adj.有益的；有利可图的', '1. Betty believed yoga was a very profitable exercise. 贝蒂认为瑜伽是一项非常有益的锻炼。 2. We hope the transaction may lead to a mutually profitable connection between us. 我方希望此次交易能导致对贵我双方有益的联系。 3. The signs bid fair for a profitable deal. 迹象表明可能是一笔有利可图的买卖。 4. Growing grapes for wine became very profitable. 种植葡萄生产葡萄酒变得非常有利可图。', '副词: profitably 名词: profitability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('proclaim', '[prə\'kleɪm]', 'vt.正式宣布；声明；表明；赞扬', '1. The president proclaimed that a new currency would be issued. 总统宣布将发行新货币。 2. She did not proclaim her intention. 她没有把自己的意图明说出来。 3. He was impelled to proclaim his doctrine. 他不得不宣扬他的教义。 4. His accent proclaimed that he was an American. 他的口音表明他是一个美国人。', '形容词: proclamatory 名词: proclaimer 过去式: proclaimed 过去分词: proclaimed 现在分词: proclaiming 第三人称单数: proclaims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dairy', '[\'deri]', 'n.牛奶场；乳品店；乳制品；地方小店 adj.牛奶的；乳制品的', '1. Milk, butter and cheese are brought in here from dairy farms . 牛奶、奶油、奶酪从牛奶场运到这里。 2. With the newly-imported equipment, the dairy can upgrade their milk to the required standard. 有了新进口的设备，乳品厂可以使新生产的牛奶达到要求。 3. The yogurt sold by this dairy is delicious. 这家乳品店出售的酸奶非常好喝。 4. Go and buy me some cleese at the dairy. 去乳品店帮我买些奶酷。 5. The dairy cattle are going to come in. 奶牛要产仔了。', '名词复数: dairies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('barren', '[\'bærən]', 'adj.贫瘠的；无效的；不育的 n.荒地', '1. No one could raise crops on this barren land. 没人能够在这么贫瘠的土地上种庄稼。 2. Life is a barren field frozen with snow. 生命就像是被雪覆盖的荒芜土地。 3. We shall turn this piece of barren land into wheat fields. 我们要把这块不毛之地变为麦田。 4. He was engaged in a barren argument with Paul. 他在同保罗作无用的争论。', '副词: barrenly 名词: barrenness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mute', '[mjuːt]', 'n.哑子；弱音器；默音字母 adj.哑的；沉默的；无声的 vt.减音；减弱 vi.(鸟)排泄', '1. He\'s a deaf mute and cannot tell anyone secret. 他是个聋哑人，不会把他们的秘密告诉任何人。 2. He has been passing himself off as a deaf - mute . 他一直装聋作哑。 3. You need get a mute on your guitar to make the tune soft. 你得给吉他安个弱音器好让音柔和一点。 4. The letter \"e\" in \"mouse\" is mute. “mouse”中的字母“e”不发音。 5. He tried to speak but he was still mute. 他尽力想说，却仍然哑口无声。 6. Please mute a music instrument. 请减低乐器的声音。', '副词: mutely 比较级: muter 最高级: mutest 名词: muteness 过去式: muted 过去分词: muted 现在分词: muting 第三人称单数: mutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prototype', '[\'proʊtətaɪp]', 'n.原型；范例；雏形', '1. The strange mechanical device is the prototype of modern cars. 这个奇怪的机械装置是现代汽车的原型。 2. Designers have built a working prototype of the car. 设计者已经制造了汽车的工作原型。 3. This is the prototype for future school buildings. 这是未来的学校建筑的蓝本。 4. He is the prototype of good breeding. 他是具有良好教养的典范。', '形容词: prototypal');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('roof', '[ruːf]', 'n.屋顶；顶 vt.覆盖；给 ... 覆以屋顶', '1. The wind was whispering in the roof. 屋顶上风声飒飒。 2. Has your roof a sharp slant? 你的屋顶是否有一个陡峭的斜面？ 3. Snow sifted through the crack in the roof into the room. 雪从屋顶上的裂缝飘进屋里。 4. The stone made a dent in the roof of my car. 我的汽车顶让石头砸了个坑。 5. We\'re going to roof in the yard to make a garage. 我们打算将院子加盖屋顶建成一个车库。', '过去式: roofed 过去分词: roofed 现在分词: roofing 第三人称单数: roofs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disaster', '[dɪ\'zæstər]', 'n.灾难', '1. They had led the country into economic disaster. 他们把国家带入了经济灾难中。 2. The disaster caused him to waver in his faith. 这件灾难使他对信仰发生了动摇。 3. He spoke darkly of possible future disaster. 他悲观地说将来可能大难临头。 4. We are all pervaded with a sense of disaster. 我们普遍有大祸降临的感觉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('directly', '[də\'rektli]', 'adv.直接地；立即；正好地；完全 conj.<英>一...就...', '1. He answered me very directly and openly. 他非常直接坦率地回答了我。 2. They bought the machine directly from the manufacturer. 他们直接从厂商那里购买了这台机器。 3. I\'ll be there directly. 我立刻到那。 4. He should be here directly if you can wait a moment. 如果你能多等一会儿的话，他应该很快就会到的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('swell', '[swel]', 'v.（使）膨胀；（使）鼓起；（使）增长 n.增大；膨胀；肿胀；汹涌 adj.<口>很棒的；时髦的；一流的', '1. The hills swell gradually up from the plain. 山丘逐渐由平原膨胀起来。 2. Tom had a fall and his under lip began to swell up. 汤姆跌了一跤，下唇开始肿起。 3. The budget deficit could swell further over the next few years. 未来几年内财政赤字可能会有更多增长。 4. The groups change more swiftly, swell with new arrivals, dissolve and form in the same breath. 人群的变化越来越快，忽而随着新来的客人而增大，忽而分散后又立即重新组合。', '比较级: sweller 最高级: swellest 过去式: swelled 过去分词: swelled/swollen 现在分词: swelling 第三人称单数: swells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intensity', '[ɪn\'tensəti]', 'n.强度；强烈；紧张', '1. The pain increased in intensity. 疼痛越来越剧烈。 2. The poem showed great intensity of feeling. 这篇韵文表现出强烈的激情。 3. I was surprised by the intensity of his anxiety. 我对他的极度焦虑感到吃惊。 4. The strike is growing in intensity. 罢工日益加剧。', '名词复数: intensities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('complicate', '[\'kɑːmplɪkeɪt]', 'v.使复杂化；使起纠纷 adj.复杂的', '1. There is no need to complicate matters. 没有必要使问题复杂化。 2. He always likes to complicate simple matters. 他总喜欢把简单的事情复杂化。 3. This text is more complicate than we can imagine. 这篇课文比我们想象的还要复杂。 4. My brother can understand the most complicate circuit diagrams. 再复杂的线路图哥哥都能看懂。', '过去式: complicated 过去分词: complicated 现在分词: complicating 第三人称单数: complicates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('melody', '[\'melədi]', 'n.旋律；曲子；曲调；美妙的音乐', '1. The melody still rang in her ears. 那个旋律仍然在她的耳际荡。 2. The organist played a famous melody. 这位管风琴手演奏了一首著名的曲子。 3. He played a delightful melody on his flute. 他用笛子吹奏了欢快的曲调。 4. The song has plaintive melody. 这首歌曲的曲调悲伤。', '名词复数: melodies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('maths', '[mæθs]', 'n.数学 =mathematics（英）.', '1. The teacher will test us in maths. 老师将测验我们数学。 2. That maths exam I took was a regular brain drain. 绞尽脑汁的数学测验，我真是绞尽了脑汁。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reservation', '[ˌrezər\'veɪʃn]', 'n.预定；保留意见', '1. I\'d like to make a reservation. 我想订票。 2. I\'ll arrive late, but please keep my reservation. 我会晚一点到达，请保留所预订的房间。 3. Do you require a deposit to confirm a reservation? 确定预定的旅馆房间要不要付定金？ 4. They accepted the proposal without reservation. 他们无保留地接受了这个建议。', '名词: reservationist');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dress', '[dres]', 'n.服装；女装 v.打扮；穿衣；穿着；给（某人）穿衣', '1. She wears a beautiful evening dress. 她穿着一件漂亮的晚礼服。 2. She wore a diamond clip on her new dress. 她在新衣服上戴了一枚钻石别针。 3. They tried to dress him up as a\"national hero\". 他们想把他打扮成一个“民族英雄”。 4. She always dresses in black. 她总穿着黑衣服。', '过去式: dressed 过去分词: dressed 现在分词: dressing 第三人称单数: dresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('misery', '[\'mɪzəri]', 'n.痛苦；悲惨的境遇；苦难', '1. War necessarily causes misery and waste. 战争必然造成痛苦和破坏。 2. He was doomed to undergo another misery. 他注定要经历另一场痛苦。 3. One usually associates poverty with misery. 人们一说到贫穷，常常就联想起悲惨的境遇。 4. He endured agonies of loneliness and misery. 他忍受着寂寞和贫穷的折磨。', '名词复数: miseries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tumour', '[\'tuːmər]', 'n.<英>肿瘤 =tumor（美）', '1. A benign tumour will not cause you any fatal harm. 良性肿瘤不会对你有致命的伤害。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glove', '[ɡlʌv]', 'n.手套 vt.给 ... 戴手套', '1. It\'s getting cool and I have to take out my woolen gloves. 天气变冷了，我不得不把毛线手套拿出来了。 2. The finger of my glove has a hole. 我手套的指头处有个洞。 3. I rarely lose a left-hand glove. 我很少脱下左手手套。 4. I showed the customer the glove section. 我给那位顾客指出了卖手套的地方。 5. The mother carefully gloved the little baby. 这位母亲细心地给婴儿戴上手套。', '过去式: gloved 过去分词: gloved 现在分词: gloving 第三人称单数: gloves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('solemn', '[\'sɑːləm]', 'adj.庄严的；严肃的；隆重的', '1. The ceremony proceeded in a solemn atmosphere. 仪式在庄严的气氛中进行。 2. They watched the solemn ceremony. 他们观看那庄严的仪式。 3. He looked at her with a solemn expression. 他表情严肃地望着她。 4. Her solemn face told them that the news was bad. 她严肃的表情告诉他们那是坏消息。', '副词: solemnly 名词: solemnness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('encyclopedia', '[ɪnˌsaɪklə\'piːdiə]', 'n.百科全书', '1. We bought a multimedia encyclopedia. 我们买了一套多媒体百科全书。 2. This encyclopedia is truly a compendium of knowledge. 这部百科全书真正是知识宝库。 3. A dictionary explains words and an encyclopedia explains facts. 词典解释词义，百科全书解释事物。 4. The new encyclopedia runs to several thousand pages. 这部新的百料全书总共有数千页。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gift', '[ɡɪft]', 'n.礼物；赠品 n.天赋；才能 vt.赋予；赠送', '1. He gave me a necklace as an anniversary gift. 他给我一条项链作为周年纪念礼物。 2. At that price it\'s an absolute gift! 那个价钱，纯粹是白给。 3. He has a gift for music. 他有音乐天赋。 4. You have a marvelous gift for science. 你有科学方面的非凡天赋。 5. Man is the only creature that is gifted with speech. 人类是唯一被赋予语言能力的动物。', '过去式: gifted 过去分词: gifted 现在分词: gifting 第三人称单数: gifts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('terminate', '[\'tɜːmɪneɪt]', 'v.结束；终止；满期；达到终点', '1. Communist Party of China terminated the rule of feudal landlord class. 中国共产党结束了封建地主阶级的统治。 2. Your contract has been terminated. 你的合同已经被终止。 3. We have to terminate this contract. 我们不得不终止这个合同。 4. The contract will terminate soon. 契约快要期满了。', '过去式: terminated 过去分词: terminated 现在分词: terminating 第三人称单数: terminates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('original', '[ə\'rɪdʒənl]', 'adj.原始的；最初的；有独创性的；原版的 n.原版；真品；怪人；有独创性的人 n.起源', '1. Our original plan was to go to Spain, but it was too expensive. 我们的原始计划是去西班牙,但是去那里太贵了。 2. I prefer your original plan to these. 我认为你最初的计划比这些都要好。 3. His designs are highly original. 他的设计独树一帜。 4. This is the original painting, and the others are copies. 这画是原作,其他的是复制品。 5. The Greek translation is faithful to the Hebrew original. 希腊语翻译很忠实于希伯来原文。 6. Fujian Province is the original and major production region of jasmine tea. 福建省是茉莉花茶的起源地和主产区。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cough', '[kɔːf]', 'v.咳嗽；咳 n.咳嗽', '1. Cover your mouth when you cough. 咳嗽时要捂上嘴。 2. I cough a great deal last night. 我昨夜咳嗽得很厉害。 3. She cough to give him the hint that he shall go. 她咳了一声，向他暗示他该走了。 4. You really ought to/should do something about that cough! 你咳嗽那麽厉害，真得治一治了！', '过去式: coughed 过去分词: coughed 现在分词: coughing 第三人称单数: coughs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('threaten', '[\'θretn]', 'v.威胁；恐吓；似将发生', '1. The rebels threatened to seize civilian hostages. 叛乱分子威胁要扣押平民为人质。 2. The strikers were threatened with dismissal if they did not return to work. 罢工者受到威胁说，如果他们不复工，就会被解雇。 3. They threatened him with a law suit. 他们以控告来恐吓他。 4. The black clouds threatened rain. 乌云密布预示着将要下雨。', '副词: threateningly 名词: threatener 过去式: threatened 过去分词: threatened 现在分词: threatening 第三人称单数: threatens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gender', '[\'dʒendər]', 'n.性；性别', '1. German has three genders. 德语中有三性。 2. The male and female genders are equal. 男性和女性是平等的。 3. Was it gender discrimination or were the female students simply superior writers? 是性别歧视还是女生天生就是擅长于写作呢? 4. Native English speakers are more gender blind when they mention their cousins. 在涉及表亲的时候,英语母语的人更容易混淆性别。', '形容词: genderless 过去式: gendered 过去分词: gendered 现在分词: gendering 第三人称单数: genders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('imaginative', '[ɪ\'mædʒɪnətɪv]', 'adj.富于想象力的', '1. Scott was an imaginative writer. 司格特是位富于想象力的作家。 2. Money still talks, but in more imaginative ways. 金钱仍然是万能的，不过是通过更加富于想象力的方式。', '副词: imaginatively 名词: imaginativeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contract', '[\'kɑːntrækt]', 'n.合同；婚约；合约；契约 v.缩小；订合同；缩短；感染（疾病）；招致', '1. They had set a term to the contract. 他们已给合同定了期限。 2. Families sought favourable alliances, either by marriage or contract. 各个家庭通过婚姻或者婚约来建立有力的亲缘关系。 3. Several companies will bid for the contract. 数家公司要投标争取合约。 4. He managed to disengage himself from the contract. 他成功地为自己解除了契约义务。 5. The heat contracted the woollen garment. 高温让羊毛衣缩小了。', '形容词: contractible 名词: contractibility 过去式: contracted 过去分词: contracted 现在分词: contracting 第三人称单数: contracts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('where', '[wer]', 'adv.在哪里；在那个地方 conj.在 ... 地方', '1. Where did she get the news? 她从哪儿得到这个消息的？ 2. I know a place where you can have a picnic. 我知道一个你可以野餐的地方。 3. We then moved to Paris, where we lived for six years. 我们後来搬到巴黎 4. Don\'t leave it where the kids can reach it. 不要把它放在孩子们能够到的地方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invert', '[ɪn\'vɜːrt]', 'v.倒置；反转；颠倒 adj.转化的 n.颠倒物；[心]同性恋者', '1. The little boy caught the insect by inverting the cup over it. 小男孩把杯子倒过来就逮住了那只昆虫。 2. The chairs were inverted on the table. 椅子被倒置过来放在了桌子上。 3. Place a plate over the cake tin and invert it. 在蛋糕烤模上盖一个盘子，然后将其翻倒过来。 4. Please invert the word order in a sentence. 请把句中的词序颠倒下。', '形容词: invertible 过去式: inverted 过去分词: inverted 现在分词: inverting 第三人称单数: inverts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('siege', '[siːdʒ]', 'n.包围；围攻', '1. The town was forced to yield after a long siege. 该城受长期围困而被迫弃守。 2. He was smitten with Mary\'s attractions and laid siege to her heart. 他被玛丽的魅力迷惑，对她苦缠不休。 3. The citizens sallied out in an attempt to break the siege. 市民们进行突击，试图冲破包围。 4. He captained the siege of Berlin. 他指挥了围攻柏林的战役。', '过去式: sieged 过去分词: sieged 现在分词: sieging 第三人称单数: sieges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dance', '[dæns]', 'n.舞会；跳舞；舞蹈；舞步 vi.跳舞；手舞足蹈 vt.跳舞；使跳跃', '1. The girls are making up for the dance. 女孩子们为了参加舞会正在化装。 2. We have fixed up a date for the dance. 我们己经定好了舞会的日期。 3. May I ask you for a dance, Lily? 莉莉,我可以请你跳舞吗? 4. Her whole life has been given to the study of dance. 她一生献身于研究舞蹈。 5. The waves danced in the sunlight. 波浪在阳光下跳舞。 6. He danced a waltz tonight. 他今晚跳了华尔兹舞。', '副词: dancingly 名词: dancer 过去式: danced 过去分词: danced 现在分词: dancing 第三人称单数: dances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('summer', '[\'sʌmər]', 'n.夏天；夏季 adj.夏季的 v.度过夏天', '1. We must use a canopy in summer. 夏天必须使用遮阳伞。 2. The stream is reduced to a mere trickle in summer. 夏天那条小河的水量减少，成了涓涓溪流。 3. The congregation of sightseers increases in the summer. 夏季，旅游观光的人增加了。 4. Summer vacation will come by and by. 暑假很快就要来到。 5. Some animals pass the summer in the sleepy state. 许多动物都是在睡眠状态中度过夏天的。', '副词: summerly 过去式: summered 过去分词: summered 现在分词: summering 第三人称单数: summers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('great', '[ɡreɪt]', 'adj.很好的；美好的；伟大的；重要的；大量的 adv.(口语)好极了', '1. What a great idea! 好主意！ 2. This cake tastes great. 这块蛋糕吃起来很不错。 3. We had a great day. 我们度过了美好的一天。 4. No one would deny that Beethoven\'s symphonies are great masterpieces. 人人都认为贝多芬的交响乐是伟大的杰作。', '副词: greatly 比较级: greater 最高级: greatest 名词: greatness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pray', '[preɪ]', 'v.祈祷；请求；恳求；祈求', '1. She prays to god to keep her son from harm. 她祈祷上帝保佑儿子平安。 2. They went to the mosque to pray. 他们去清真寺做祷告。 3. I earnestly pray for your pardon. 我恳切地请求你原谅。 4. I pray that you will have pity on my distress. 我请求你可怜可怜我的不幸遭遇。', '过去式: prayed 过去分词: prayed 现在分词: praying 第三人称单数: prays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tired', '[\'taɪərd]', 'adj.疲倦的；疲劳的；累的；厌烦的 动词tire的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. I am not in the least tired. 我一点也不疲倦。 2. If you watch too much TV, you\'ll feel tired. 如果你看电视太多,你就会感到疲劳。 3. We reached our destination, tired and hungry. 到达目的地时,我们又累又饿。 4. I was too tired to walk any further. 我累得再也走不动了。', '副词: tiredly 名词: tiredness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strength', '[streŋθ]', 'n.力气；强度；力量；长处', '1. I have hardly enough strength left to move my feet. 我连移动双脚的力气都几乎没有了。 2. In this game, you need more science than strength. 在这项比赛中，技巧比力气更重要。 3. By doing so, you can test the strength of steel. 这样做,你可以试验一下钢的强度。 4. She prayed for strength in her troubles. 她祈求(上帝)在困难时给她力量。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('swear', '[swer]', 'v.咒骂；发誓；宣誓 n.誓言；咒骂；发誓', '1. Shut up! How dare you swear at me like that! 住嘴，你竟敢那样咒骂我! 2. You have no right to swear at me like that! 你无权那样咒骂我！ 3. I swear by Almighty God that I will tell the truth. 我对万能的上帝发誓我要说真话。 4. They swore an oath to carry out their duties faithfully. 他们发誓要忠实履行自己的职责。 5. Don\'t forget your swear for me. 不要忘记你对我发过的誓言。', '名词: swearer 过去式: swore 过去分词: sworn 现在分词: swearing 第三人称单数: swears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rash', '[ræʃ]', 'n.疹子；大量 adj.鲁莽的；轻率的', '1. While you have this rash you are still infectious. 身上还有这种疹子，就仍然有传染性。 2. A rash has appeared on his body. 他身上出现了丘疹。 3. The heat brought him out in a rash. 因气温很高，他浑身长了皮疹。 4. As soon as popular songs were accepted, fans appeared in a rash 流行歌曲一被接受, 追星族就大量涌现。 5. Don\'t do anything rash. 不要鲁莽行事。', '副词: rashly 比较级: rasher 最高级: rashest 名词: rashness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brother', '[\'brʌðər]', 'n.兄弟；教友；同胞；<俚>老兄', '1. John and Peter are brothers. 约翰和彼得是兄弟。 2. The man who captained the home team is my brother. 率领主队的是我的兄弟。 3. Don\'t be so unkind to your brother. 别对你兄弟这么刻薄。 4. I always confounded him with his twin brother. 我总分不清他和他的孪生兄弟。', '名词复数: brothers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reply', '[rɪ\'plaɪ]', 'v.回答；答复；回应 n.回答；答复', '1. What a sage reply you gave! 多聪明的回答啊！ 2. He gave me no chance to reply to his question. 他没有给我回答他问题的机会。 3. I\'m rather hazy about how to reply. 我不清楚如何回答。 4. It\'s very odd that she didn\'t reply to our letter. 她没有回我们的信是件很奇怪的事。 5. Thank you for your prompt reply to our telegram. 多谢您对我们电报的即刻答复。', '名词: replier 名词复数: replies 过去式: replied 过去分词: replied 现在分词: replying 第三人称单数: replies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('register', '[\'redʒɪstər]', 'v.登记；记录；注册；挂号 n.登记簿；记录；暂存器 n.[语]语域；[音]音域通风调节设备', '1. You must register if you intend to vote. 如果你要投票选举,你就必须登记。 2. He registered the trial proceedings. 法庭速记员记录下了审判进程。 3. You must register as a member first. 你必须先注册成为会员。 4. I want this letter registered. 我想挂号邮寄这封信。 5. Would you sign the register? 请你在登记簿上签名好吗? 6. Official documents are written in formal register. 官方文件是以正式语体写成的。', '形容词: registrable 名词: registration 过去式: registered 过去分词: registered 现在分词: registering 第三人称单数: registers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crab', '[kræb]', 'n.蟹；阴虱；爱争吵的人；[植]山楂子 v.捕蟹；使横行；批评；抱怨', '1. All the shops on the seafront had crab for sale. 海滨地区的全部商店都出售蟹。 2. A crab was left stranded on the beach when the tide ebbed. 退潮时，一只蟹被困留在沙滩上。 3. My neighbor is such an old crab. 我的邻居可真是个爱争吵的人。', '名词: crabber 过去式: crabbed 过去分词: crabbed 现在分词: crabbing 第三人称单数: crabs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('waiter', '[\'weɪtər]', 'n.侍者；(男)服务员', '1. A waiter of the Japanese restaurant bowed him in. 那家日本餐馆的侍者鞠着躬将他迎了进去。 2. It is customary to tip the waiter. 给侍者小费是一种习俗。 3. He sent the waiter for a packet of cigarettes. 他让侍者去拿一盒香烟。 4. He asked the waiter to bring him a cask of sherry. 他叫侍者给他拿一桶雪利酒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('subjective', '[səb\'dʒektɪv]', 'adj.主观的', '1. His arguments were never subjective. 他的论点从来不是主观的。 2. He took a subjective view of the problem. 他用主观的方法看问题。 3. Grading of oral tests is quite subjective. 口语考试的打分是相当主观的。', '副词: subjectively 名词: subjectiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fraction', '[\'frækʃn]', 'n.小部分；少许；分数；片段', '1. Mother\'s careful with her money, and spends only a fraction of her earnings. 母亲用钱很审慎,只花自己收入很小的一部分。 2. The door opened a fraction. 门稍微开了条缝。 3. I can only pay a fraction of my bill. 我只付我的帐单的一小部分。 4. Open the window a fraction, please. 请把窗户打开一点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('barber', '[\'bɑːrbər]', 'n.理发师 vi.当理发师 vt.给…理发；修剪', '1. The barber thinned out my thick hair. 理发师把我浓密的头发削薄了一些。 2. The barber cut his hair very short. 理发师把他的头发剪得很短。 3. His father apprenticed him to a barber. 他父亲送他去当理发师的徒弟。 4. The barber bought one of his brooms, and, when he had shaved him, asked for the price of it. 当理发师给他修完面后，问了一下扫帚的价钱。 5. They sat in twos and threes on the trim barbered lawn. 他们三三两两地坐在修剪平整的草坪上。', '过去式: barbered 过去分词: barbered 现在分词: barbering 第三人称单数: barbers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cripple', '[\'krɪpl]', 'n.跛者；残废 v.削弱；使...瘫痪', '1. They helped the cripple up to the bank. 他们把那跛脚的人扶上岸。 2. It is impolite to make fun of a cripple. 取笑一个跛足是不礼貌的。 3. A long delay might cripple me in a way. 长期拖下去可能在某些方面把我拖垮了。 4. His first task was to cripple the enemy at sea. 他的首要任务是使海上的敌人失去战斗力。', '名词: crippler 过去式: crippled 过去分词: crippled 现在分词: crippling 第三人称单数: cripples');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comprise', '[kəm\'praɪz]', 'vt.构成；包含', '1. This month\'s figures are comprised in the total. 这个月的数字已包含在总数之内。 2. Fifteen separate republics comprised the Soviet Union. 苏联由十五个加盟共和国组成。 3. Fifty states comprise the Union. 五十个州组成美国。 4. Twelve departments comprise this university. 12个系组成了这所大学。', '形容词: comprisable 过去式: comprised 过去分词: comprised 现在分词: comprising 第三人称单数: comprises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('literary', '[lɪtəreri]', 'adj.文学的', '1. He is endowed with literary talent. 他有文学天分。 2. Dickens\' A Tale of Two Cities is a literary classic. 狄更斯的《双城记》是文学名著。 3. I don\'t like to read his literary criticism. 我不喜欢读他的文学批评。 4. Her poetry is full of obscure literary allusions. 他的诗里用了很多晦涩的文学典故。', '副词: literarily 名词: literariness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('detach', '[dɪ\'tætʃ]', 'vt.使分离；拆卸；派遣 [计算机] 脱离.', '1. He detached a link from a chain. 他从链子上拆下一个链环。 2. I tried to detach myself from the reality of these terrible events. 我尽力使自己从这些可怕事件的现实中摆脱出来。 3. We should detach good apples from bad. 我们必须把好的苹果与坏的分开. 4. He detached a link from a chain. 他从链子上拆下一个链环。', '形容词: detachable 副词: detachably 名词: detachability 过去式: detached 过去分词: detached 现在分词: detaching 第三人称单数: detaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sticky', '[\'stɪki]', 'adj.粘的；闷热的；困难的；令人不满意的', '1. I am uncomfortable because my body is sticky . 我身上粘粘的，很不舒服。 2. Yuanxiao is a kind of sticky round dumplings. 元宵是一种粘粘的圆的面团。 3. A hot, sticky day makes a person listless. 天气闷热使人觉得身上有气无力。 4. They put me in a sticky position. 他们将我置于一个困难的境地。', '副词: stickily 比较级: stickier 最高级: stickiest 名词: stickiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fake', '[feɪk]', 'adj.假的 n.骗子；假货；欺骗 vt.伪造；伪装 vi.假造', '1. Cops arrest 8 men who manufacture and sale fake collage notice . 警察在本月初逮捕了8名伪造和贩卖假大学录取通知书的人. 2. I can\'t believe he sold me a lousy fake watch! 我真不敢相信,他居然卖给我一块糟糕的假表! 3. He looked like a postman but he was really a fake. 他看上去像个邮递员，但实际上是假冒的。 4. On closer examination the painting was proved to be a fake. 再经仔细观察，证实那幅画是膺品。 5. He faked his father\'s signature. 他伪造父亲的签字。 6. Every politician has to fake a little. 每个政治家都是有点矫揉造作。', '过去式: faked 过去分词: faked 现在分词: faking 第三人称单数: fakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('biology', '[baɪ\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.生物学；(一个地区的全部)生物；生物群落', '1. He specializes biology. 他主修生物学。 2. We have a biology lesson tomorrow. 明天我们有堂生物学课。 3. He is an environmentalist with a passion of the biology and geography of the region. 他是一个环保人士，对这个地区的生物和地理很有热情。 4. He is knowledgeable about the biology of the honeybee. 他对蜜蜂的生活规律知之甚多。', '名词: biologist');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dwell', '[dwel]', 'vi.居住；存在；冥想；详细阐述', '1. He decided to dwell on our island. 他决定到我们的岛上居住。 2. I own two flats where I used to dwell alternately. 我拥有两个居所并一直交替地居住。 3. How his words dwell in my mind! 他的一席话在我的脑海里经久难忘。 4. They dwelled in joy. 他们沉浸于欢乐之中。', '名词: dweller 过去式: dwelt/dwelled 过去分词: dwelt/dwelled 现在分词: dwelling 第三人称单数: dwells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('panorama', '[ˌpænə\'ræmə]', 'n.全景；全景画；概观；一连串景象或事物', '1. promise graciously 2. As we stood at the top of the mountain, a beautiful panorama spread out before us. 我们登上山顶时，一幅美丽的景色展现在我们的面前。 3. The book presents a panorama of British history since the Middle Ages. 该书概述了中世纪以来的英国历史。 4. Henry watched the panorama of pass people with wide eyes. 亨利观看着一连串过往的人群。', '形容词: panoramic 副词: panoramically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('apart', '[ə\'pɑːrt]', 'adv.相距；分开地；分别地 adj.分开的；分离的', '1. The two villages are three miles apart. 这两个村子相距三英里。 2. He took the watch apart to repair it. 他把手表拆开来修理。 3. She lives apart from her family. 她跟家人分开住。 4. I can\'t tell the twins apart. 我辨认不出这对双胞胎。 5. At that time we were never apart. 那时我们从不分开。', '名词: apartness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slender', '[\'slendər]', 'adj.细长的；苗条的；微薄的；少量的', '1. It was a long, slender stick of vivid yellow. 那是一根鲜黄色的又细又长的粉笔。 2. All girls want to be slender. 所有女孩都希望苗条。 3. She was slender and had long dark hair. 她身材苗条，有一头长长的黑发。 4. The daughter was to have but a slender provision. 女儿只能得到一份菲薄的嫁妆。', '副词: slenderly 比较级: slenderer 最高级: slenderest 名词: slenderness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('summarize', '[\'sʌməraɪz]', 'v.概述；摘要而言', '1. She wrote something to summarize her hypothesis. 她写了一些东西来概述她的假设。 2. I will summarize what I have done. 我将概述我所做的事情。 3. The authors summarize their views in the introduction. 作者在介绍中概括了他们的观点。 4. To summarize, simplicity is the best art. 总之，简洁是最好的艺术。', '名词: summarization 过去式: summarized 过去分词: summarized 现在分词: summarizing 第三人称单数: summarizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cluster', '[\'klʌstər]', 'n.群；簇；丛；串 v.群集；丛生；使成群', '1. A cluster of tourists are waiting for their tour guide. 一群游客正在等他们的导游。 2. You can see stars in clusters in the night sky. 你可以看到夜空中的星群。 3. You can see clusters of berries in the garden. 花园里能见到一簇簇浆果。 4. You can see ivy growing in thick clusters anywhere. 到哪儿都能看见成丛生长的常春藤。 5. The men clustered together round the fire and sang songs. 人们聚集在篝火周围唱歌。', '过去式: clustered 过去分词: clustered 现在分词: clustering 第三人称单数: clusters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pet', '[pet]', 'n.宠物；受宠的人 adj.宠爱的 v.爱抚；亲抚', '1. My daughter keeps a rabbit as pet. 我的女儿养了一只兔子当做宠物。 2. She is the teacher\'s pet. 她是老师的宠儿。 3. The little girl cuddled her pet cat. 这个小女孩搂抱着她的宠物猫。 4. Talk quietly to your kitten and gently pet her. 温柔的对它说话，轻轻的抚摩它。', '名词: petter 过去式: petted 过去分词: petted 现在分词: petting 第三人称单数: pets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('patriotic', '[ˌpeɪtri\'ɑːtɪk]', 'adj.爱国的', '1. They had a pile of stuff put out by some kind of East-Prussian patriotic blood-and-soil gang. 他们手头上有一大堆材料，是东普鲁士一帮标榜爱国的纳粹分子散发出来的。 2. They are still sceptical about socialism, but they are patriotic when it comes to facing imperialism. 他们对社会主义还有怀疑，但是在帝国主义面前，他们还是爱国的。', '副词: patriotically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('breast', '[brest]', 'n.乳房；胸脯 vt.(以胸)对着', '1. The little baby can take nourishment from the breast. 小婴儿可以从乳房中吸取营养。 2. The baby was being nursed at its mother\'s breast. 那个孩子正在吃母亲的奶。 3. The bird\'s breast is flecked with brown. 这只鸟胸前有棕色斑点。 4. They had chicken breast for supper. 他们晚饭吃鸡胸肉。 5. Who is the first to breast the tape? 谁第一个到终点的?', '过去式: breasted 过去分词: breasted 现在分词: breasting 第三人称单数: breasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('harassment', '[hə\'ræsmənt]', 'n.骚扰；困扰', '1. The company prohibits any form of harassment. 公司禁止任何形式的骚扰行为。 2. There is a report about a sexual harassment in the office on this newspaper. 今天的报纸上有一篇关于办公室里的性骚扰的报道。 3. African-Americans have been complaining about police harassment for years. 非洲裔美国人不断地抱怨警察这些年来对他们的骚扰。 4. Authorities generally step up surveillance and harassment of critics of the government on such anniversaries to guard against unrest. 主管当局在如此的周年通常加速政府的批评家的监视和困扰预防不安的状态。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('garage', '[ɡə\'rɑːʒ]', 'n.汽车修理厂；车库 vt.把 ... 放入车库', '1. He sent his car to the garage for repair. 他把汽车送到修车厂修理。 2. My car broke down and had to be towed to a garage. 我的汽车出故障了，得拉到修理厂去。 3. There is a garage built onto the side of the house. 这所房子的一侧建有一个车库。 4. We can\'t afford a car, not to mention the fact that we have no garage. 我们买不起汽车，没有车库的事就更不必说了。', '形容词: garageable 过去式: garaged 过去分词: garaged 现在分词: garaging 第三人称单数: garages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('degenerate', '[dɪ\'dʒenəreɪt]', 'v.退化；堕落 adj.堕落的；退化的 n.堕落的人', '1. Watching TV too much would degenerate your brain. 多看电视会使你的头脑退化。 2. His health is degenerating rapidly. 他的健康状况迅速恶化。 3. Will too much freedom make them degenerate? 太多的自由会令他们堕落吗? 4. He didn\'t let riches and luxury make him degenerate. 他不因财富和奢华而自甘堕落。 5. The thief was a degenerate member of a fine family. 那小偷是优秀家族的堕落的成员。 6. This degenerate seduced my daughter! 这个道德败坏的人勾引我的女儿！', '副词: degenerately 名词: degenerateness 过去式: degenerated 过去分词: degenerated 现在分词: degenerating 第三人称单数: degenerates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diamond', '[\'daɪəmənd]', 'n.钻石；菱形；棒球内场；纸牌的方块 vt.用钻石装饰', '1. She wore a diamond clip on her new dress. 她在新衣服上戴了一枚钻石别针。 2. The diamond ring on her finger glittered in the light. 她手指上的钻石戒指在灯光下闪闪发光。 3. Her bedroom curtains have a diamond pattern. 她卧室的窗帘有菱形的图案。 4. Mr Smith laid off a baseball diamond on the vacant lot. 史密斯先生在空地上划出棒球内场的界线。', '过去式: diamonded 过去分词: diamonded 现在分词: diamonding 第三人称单数: diamonds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ball', '[bɔːl]', 'n.球；球状物；炮弹；舞会；愉快的经历；<口>胆量；胡说；（复）睾丸 v.使成球状；呈球状；<俚>性交', '1. The cat made little rushes to and fro after the ball. 猫追着球跑过来跑过去。 2. She rolled the socks into a ball. 她把袜子卷成一团。 3. I cut up the meat for cooking meat balls. 我把肉剁碎后做肉丸子。 4. His left arm was shattered into matches by a cannon ball. 他的左臂被一炮弹击碎。 5. She balled the letter into a wad. 她将信揉成一团。', '过去式: balled 过去分词: balled 现在分词: balling 第三人称单数: balls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fortnight', '[\'fɔːrtnaɪt]', 'n.两星期；十四天', '1. It\'s a fortnight to National Day. 离国庆节还有两星期。 2. The patient lived out another fortnight. 病人又活了两星期。 3. I\'d get a sickening sense of dread for the fortnight leading up to them, knowing that I would become a sleep-deprived grumpy, spotty hermit. 十四天的夜班后我发现感到胆战心惊的害怕，我很清楚的知道自己会变成一个睡眠不足的，性情乖戾情绪不稳的隐士。 4. A fortnight has fourteen days. 两周有十四天。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('incline', '[ɪn\'klaɪn]', 'n.倾斜；斜坡；斜面 v.(使)倾向于；向前弯；(使)倾斜', '1. The houses followed the curve of the road, which wound up a slight incline. 这些房子沿着道路有些倾斜的曲线而建。 2. She plunged instantly down the slippery incline. 她立刻沿着光滑的斜坡向下跌落。 3. Galileo rolled small metal balls down the incline. 伽利略让小金属球从斜面滚下。 4. I incline to his opinion on this matter. 对这件事我倾向于他的观点。', '名词: incliner 过去式: inclined 过去分词: inclined 现在分词: inclining 第三人称单数: inclines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('renaissance', '[\'renəsɑːns]', 'n.文艺复兴；再生', '1. Her book captures the quintessence of Renaissance humanism. 她的书抓住了文艺复兴时期人文主义的精髓。 2. Florence is the shrine of the Renaissance. 佛罗伦萨是文艺复兴的圣地。 3. These are the cultural legacies of the Renaissance. 这些是文艺复兴时期的文化遗产。 4. Leonardo da Vinci is a famous artist in the Italian Renaissance. 利奥纳多·达·芬奇是意大利文艺复兴时期的一位知名画家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('general', '[\'dʒenrəl]', 'adj.普遍的；全面的；一般性的；大致的；笼统的；常规的；总的；首席的 n.将军；一般', '1. The announcement was met with general rejoicing. 该项宣布受到普遍的欢迎。 2. Her predictions are so general that they could apply to anybody. 她的预测很全面,放之四海而皆准。 3. As a general rule, prices follow demands. 一般而言,物价随需求而变化。 4. They gave a general description of the man. 他们对这个男人作了大致的描述。 5. The general is a respectable man. 那位将军是个令人肃然起敬的人物。', '名词: generalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('justice', '[\'dʒʌstɪs]', 'n.公平；公正；正义；司法；法官；法律制裁', '1. I won\'t dispute the justice of his remarks. 我不怀疑他的话是公平合理的。 2. Marriage is, first of all, a contract which must be governed by justice. 婚姻首先是一种契约，它必须以公正为制约。 3. Justice triumphs in the end. 正义终将得胜。 4. British justice works on the premise that an accused person is innocent until he\'s proved guilty. 英国司法运作的前提是被告在被证明有罪之前是清白的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lace', '[leɪs]', 'n.鞋带；饰带；花边；缎带 v.系带子；饰以花边；把酒搀入；<口>抨击', '1. He stopped to do up his shoe lace. 他停下来把鞋带系上。 2. My shoe lace keeps coming undone. 我的鞋带老是松开。 3. My daughter wears a dress embellished with lace and ribbons today. 今天我女儿穿了一件有花边和饰带的连衣裙。 4. She wears a dress with delicate lace. 她穿了一件带有精致花边的裙子。 5. If you don\'t lace up your shoes, you\'ll trip over. 如果你不系好鞋带，你会被绊倒的。', '形容词: laceless 名词: lacer 过去式: laced 过去分词: laced 现在分词: lacing 第三人称单数: laces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('royal', '[\'rɔɪəl]', 'adj.盛大的；皇家的；高贵的；第一流的；堂皇的 n.顶桅帆；王室成员，贵族；纸张规格（书写纸19×24寸/印刷纸20×25寸）', '1. Two men carried the standard in the royal parade. 在盛大的游行队伍中, 两个男子打着旗子。 2. The royal wedding was an occasion of great festivity. 皇室婚礼是喜庆的盛事。 3. Britain has always had a large navy, called the Royal Navy. 英国一直有一支强大的海军，称为皇家海军。 4. My life is like a tapestry of rich and royal hue. 我的生活就象那色彩高贵而又丰富的挂毯。 5. Like Princess Grace of Monaco, Diana was a celebrity royal. 和摩纳哥的公主一样，黛安娜是一位著名的王室成员。', '副词: royally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bonus', '[\'boʊnəs]', 'n.红利；意外所得之物；奖金；【篮】追加罚篮', '1. The firm offered her a generous bonus as a sweetener. 公司提出给她一笔可观的花红借以拉拢她。 2. He received a box of cookies as a bonus when he bought coffee at the shop. 他在商店买咖啡时,意外地得到了一盒免费赠送的饼干。 3. The warm weather in such a freezing winter has been a real bonus. 这么寒冷的冬天有这样暖和的天气真是令人喜出望外。 4. The firm repaid her hard work with a bonus. 公司发给她奖金以酬谢她的辛勤工作。', '名词复数: bonuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outer', '[\'aʊtər]', 'adj.外部的；外面的', '1. This is compensated for an outer impressiveness. 这一点由外部的感人情景得到了补偿。 2. Outer enclosure shall not crack to the extent that the cells or any protective devices are exposed. 外部的粘着处不能裂开至裸露出电池或保护装置。 3. But you can use a swab or cloth to clean the outer part of the ear. 但是你可以用棉签或者布把你耳朵外面的部分擦干净。 4. The outer door opened.There stood Inspector Hornberg. 外面的门开了，霍恩伯格督学站在那里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('opening', '[\'oʊpnɪŋ]', 'n.开口；开始；张开；开幕；空缺 adj.开头的 动词open的现在分词.', '1. He scraped through the narrow opening. 他勉强钻过狭窄的开口处。 2. He put a gate across the opening in the fence. 他在围墙的开口处安了一个门。 3. The book\'s opening is dull, but the last chapters are interesting. 那本书的开始部分枯燥乏味,但最后几章很有意思。 4. The establishment of the new China marks the opening of a new age. 新中国的成立标志着一个新纪元的开始。 5. His opening remarks are applauded by the audience. 他的开场白受到听众的鼓掌欢迎。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cry', '[kraɪ]', 'v.哭；(大声)叫喊；(强烈)要求 n.叫声；哭；喊', '1. She cried with grief when she heard news of her friend\'s death. 听到朋友死亡的消息，她难过地哭了。 2. She began to cry in the face of failure. 面对失败，她开始哭了起来。 3. He cried that he had found the key. 他大声地叫喊找到了钥匙。 4. The girl in the river is crying for help. 掉进河里的女孩正喊救命呢。 5. Very soon he heard a raven cry outside. 很快他就听见了外面乌鸦的叫声。', '名词复数: cries 过去式: cried 过去分词: cried 现在分词: crying 第三人称单数: cries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('locker', '[\'lɑːkər]', 'n.更衣箱；储物柜；冷藏室；上锁的人', '1. After opening the locker please watch your belongings carefully, so they will not be misplaced. 请您在打开更衣箱后，看管好自己的物品，以防丢失。 2. Ender closed his locker and tried to reopen it. 安德关上他的储物柜试着再次打开。 3. There is a locker charge of one dollar. 寄物柜收费一美元。 4. We have to find the locker to get the key. 我们必须找上锁的人拿钥匙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('landlord', '[\'lændlɔːrd]', 'n.地主；房东', '1. The farmhands gave the landlord a sound beating. 雇工们把这地主痛打了一顿。 2. Her husband was driven to death by the landlord. 她丈夫就是被地主逼死的。 3. I owe the landlord one hundred dollars. 我欠房东一百美元。 4. The council brought pressure to bear on the landlord to improve his property. 市政会向房主施加了压力，促使其改善房子的居住条件。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oriental', '[ˌɔːri\'entl]', 'adj.东方的；东方人的；（宝石）贵重的；优质的 n.东方人', '1. He specializes in oriental history. 他专门研究东方史。 2. She has studied the cultures of Oriental countries. 她研究过东方各国的文化。 3. China is an oriental country with a long history. 中国是一个有着悠久历史的东方国家。 4. This oriental legend is fascinating. 这个东方传说很吸引人。 5. The Oriental is proficient in the ingredients. 东方人对成分熟练。', '副词: orientally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cigar', '[sɪ\'ɡɑːr]', 'n.雪茄烟', '1. He exhaled a billow of cigar smoke. 他吐出一股雪茄烟。 2. Your cigar tinctures the room with an awful smell. 你吸雪茄烟弄得满屋子都是臭味。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rotten', '[\'rɑːtn]', 'adj.腐烂的；腐朽的；<口>极坏的；讨厌的 adv.非常', '1. One smell of the rotten meat was enough! 这腐烂的肉闻一下就够受的了。 2. This place has an odious smell; something must be rotten. 这个地方有一股臭味，一定有东西腐烂了。 3. The wood was so rotten that you could put your finger through it. 这木料腐朽了,你可以用手指戳穿它。 4. They are contaminating the minds of our young people with these rotten ideas. 他们正用这些腐朽的思想污染着我们青年人的头脑。 5. The child is spoiled rotten. 这个小孩被宠坏了。', '副词: rottenly 比较级: rottener 最高级: rottenest 名词: rottenness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glance', '[ɡlæns]', 'v.扫视；匆匆一看；一瞥；反光；闪烁；掠过 n.一瞥；扫视', '1. She glanced round the room before she left. 她略微环视了一下房间才离开。 2. I\'m just going to glance over these documents, then we can go. 我再看一下这些文件，然后我们就可以走了。 3. On the bus I always manage to glance at the headline in the newspaper. 在公共汽车上我总能设法匆匆看一眼报纸大标题。 4. He glanced at the envelope and recognized his uncle\'s handwriting. 他瞥了一眼那个信封,认出是他叔父的笔迹。 5. He gave her an admiring glance. 他向她投以敬慕的一瞥。', '过去式: glanced 过去分词: glanced 现在分词: glancing 第三人称单数: glances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bother', '[\'bɑːðər]', 'v.烦扰；使恼怒；使不安；费心 n.麻烦；烦扰；焦急', '1. I\'ve no time to bother with such things. 我没时间为这种事烦恼。 2. Don\'t write anything that will bother the censor. 你可别写什么给检查员找麻烦的话。 3. It bothers me that he can be so insensitive. 他这样麻木不仁，我心里很不痛快。 4. The problem has been bothering me for weeks. 那问题已经困扰了我几个星期。 5. Oh,would you mind? I hate to be a bother. 哦，你不介意吗?我不愿麻烦别人。', '过去式: bothered 过去分词: bothered 现在分词: bothering 第三人称单数: bothers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('somehow', '[\'sʌmhaʊ]', 'adv.以某种方式；不知怎么地', '1. We must make up for the lost time somehow. 我们必须以某种方式把损失的时间补上。 2. I wish I can repay you somehow for your kindness. 我希望我能以某种方式报答您的好意。 3. He could have finished it on schedule, but somehow he fell behind. 他原本能按预定进度做完这件事的，但不知怎地却落后了。 4. Somehow or other, the baby burst into tears. 那个婴儿不知为什么大哭起来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spur', '[spɜːr]', 'n.支脉；刺激；马刺；鞭策 vt.刺激；鞭策；促进', '1. She went to London on the spur of the moment. 她一时兴起就到伦敦去了。 2. International competition was a spur to modernization. 国际竞争是实现现代化的动力。 3. A good heart horse often needs a good spur. 好马常需好靴刺。 4. The thought of the prize was the spur for the team. 夺取锦标的想法是该队的动力。 5. What spurred her to do that? 是什么促使她那么干的？', '过去式: spurred 过去分词: spurred 现在分词: spurring 第三人称单数: spurs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('convention', '[kən\'venʃn]', 'n.大会；协定；惯例；公约', '1. The convention looms as political battle. 这场大会将是一场政治角斗。 2. Delegates will be picked at a convention. 代表将在大会上选出。 3. This convention results in no ambiguity. 这个协定不会导致误解。 4. The countries all agreed to sign the convention. 各国都同意签署这项协定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conscientious', '[ˌkɒnʃɪ\'enʃəs]', 'adj.认真的；谨慎的；负责的', '1. The janitor is very conscientious. 那个管理员很认真。 2. He\'s changed into a conscientious worker. 他已成为一个工作认真的人了。 3. Be more conscientious about your work. 要更谨慎做你的工作。 4. This essay is a most conscientious piece of work. 这篇论文是精雕细刻的工作.', '副词: conscientiously 名词: conscientiousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('space', '[speɪs]', 'n.空间；处所；太空；空地；空闲；空格；间隙 v.留间隔；分隔；走神；忘记', '1. There is plenty of space to move about. 这里有很大的活动空间。 2. I only have a small working space. 我只有一间很小的办公室。 3. A missile was projected into space. 导弹被发射升空。 4. It\'s easier for small car to find a parking space. 小型汽车比较容易找到停车空地。 5. Space your words when you write. 写字的时候要把字均匀地隔开。', '名词: spacer 过去式: spaced 过去分词: spaced 现在分词: spacing 第三人称单数: spaces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Tuesday', '[\'tuːzdeɪ]', 'n.星期二', '1. School will begin next Tuesday. 下星期二将要开学。 2. He\'s available on Tuesday. 星期二他在。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('province', '[\'prɑːvɪns]', 'n.省', '1. British Columbia is a province of Canada. 不列颠哥伦比亚是加拿大的一个省。 2. Hangzhou is the capital city of Zhejiang Province. 杭州是浙江的省会城市。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contribute', '[kən\'trɪbjuːt]', 'vt.捐助；投稿 vi.投稿；贡献；是原因之一', '1. It was generous of her to contribute such a large sum. 她很大方，捐助了这么大笔钱。 2. She asked him to contribute a biweekly article on European affairs. 她让他每两周写一篇有关欧洲情况的文章。 3. Don\'t contribute after the closing date. 请在截止日期前投稿。 4. It is an honour to be invited to contribute to your magazine. 应邀向贵杂志投稿是一个荣誉。', '形容词: contributive 副词: contributively 名词: contributiveness 过去式: contributed 过去分词: contributed 现在分词: contributing 第三人称单数: contributes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compound', '[\'kɑːmpaʊnd]', 'n.化合物；复合词；复合物 n.院子(用围墙圈起来的场地） adj.化合的；【语】（词语等）复合的；【植】复合的；【动】群体的 vt.混合；调合；使严重；私了；【经】以复利计算 vi.妥协', '1. Water is a compound of hydrogen and oxygen. 水是氢和氧的化合物。 2. \'Bus conductor\', \'dark-haired\' and \'policeman\' are compounds. bus conductor,dark-haired和policeman都是复合词。 3. Medicines are usually compounds. 药品通常是复合物。 4. All prisoners were frog-marched (out) into the compound. 犯人都被迫反剪双臂(出来)进入院子。 5. \"Fingerprint\" is a compound word. “Fingerprint”（指纹）是一个复合词。 6. He compounded various ingredients into an effective drug. 他将各种成分混合成一种有效的药物。 7. He compounded with his creditors for a remission of what he owed. 他和他的债权人谈妥免除其债务。', '形容词: compoundable 名词: compounder 过去式: compounded 过去分词: compounded 现在分词: compounding 第三人称单数: compounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deck', '[dek]', 'n.甲板；层面；一副牌 vt.装饰；<俚>用力击倒', '1. The colonel ordered their soldiers to gather on the deck. 上校命令士兵们在甲板上集合。 2. The deck of the sailing ship was made of thick planks. 这艘帆船的甲板是用厚木板制作的。 3. The sailor suddenly saw a pirate jumping onto the deck. 那水手忽然看到一名海盗跳上了甲板。 4. Passengers may smoke only on the upper deck of the bus. 乘客只可以在公共汽车的上层吸烟。 5. She did not want to deck herself with knowledge. 她并不想把知识当装饰品。', '过去式: decked 过去分词: decked 现在分词: decking 第三人称单数: decks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brick', '[brɪk]', 'n.砖；砖块；砖状物 vt.用砖围砌（或堵）', '1. His new house was built by himself, brick by brick. 他的新房子是他自己一块砖一块砖砌起来的。 2. Her husband is a brick layer. 她丈夫是个砌砖匠。 3. He had a brick thrown at him at that meeting. 那次集会时，他的头部被一块砖头击中。 4. He bought a brick of cheese and a bottle of wine. 他买了一块乳酪和一瓶葡萄酒。 5. All the windows were bricked up. 所有的窗户都用砖堵住了。', '形容词: bricky 名词复数: bricks 过去式: bricked 过去分词: bricked 现在分词: bricking 第三人称单数: bricks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('litre', '[\'liːtər]', 'n.公升 =liter(美).', '1. The capacity of this bottle is one litre. 这个瓶子的容量是1公升。 2. A litre of gas has less mass than a litre of water. 一公升的气体质量少于一公升的水。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alternative', '[ɔːl\'tɜːrnətɪv]', 'adj.两者择一的；供选择的；非主流的 n.二者择一；供替代的选择', '1. We have the alternative plans of having a picnic or taking a boat trip. 我们在去野餐或者去乘船旅游两个计划中只能选一。 2. They are provided with the choice of two alternative flights. 有两个航班可供他们选择。 3. I\'d like to get some alternative music CDs for my niece. 我想买一些非主流的音乐唱片给我侄女。 4. I had no alternative but to accept the offer. 我除了接受该项提议之外，别无选择。', '副词: alternatively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dragon', '[\'dræɡən]', 'n.龙', '1. This jade dragon is a genuine antique. 这件玉龙是真正的古玩。 2. Dragons are described as monsters in most western countries. 在大多数西方国家，龙被认为是怪物。 3. The contour of that mountain looks like a dragon. 那座大山的轮廓看上去像一条龙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('them', '[ðəm]', 'pron.他们；她们；它们；性别不详的人（代替him或her）', '1. Let\'s go visit them. 让我们去拜访他们吧。 2. A feeling of resentment urged him to abandon them. 一种怨恨的心情促使他离开了她们。 3. Don\'t bend the wires down, it\'ll break them. 不要弯折那些线，会弄坏它们的。 4. If anyone arrives early, ask them to wait. 如果有人早到，就让他们等会儿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rip', '[rɪp]', 'v.撕裂；扯开 n.裂口；裂缝；撕裂', '1. The poster had been ripped to pieces. 那张广告画已被撕得粉碎。 2. I ripped my stocking on a nail. 一个钉子挂破了我的袜子。 3. You should rip the cover off the box first. 你首先应当把这个盒子的封套扯掉。 4. She sewed up the rip in his sleeve. 她缝好了他衣袖上的裂口。', '名词: ripper 过去式: ripped 过去分词: ripped 现在分词: ripping 第三人称单数: rips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('proof', '[pruːf]', 'n.证明；证据；校样 adj.防 ... 的；耐 ... 的 vt.检验；给 ... 做防护措施', '1. This fact is too evident to require proof. 这事实很明显, 用不着证明。 2. Have you got any proof that you own this bike? 你有什么证据证明这辆自行车是你的？ 3. There are a few misprints which I will correct in proof. 有几处印错了,我将在校样上一一改正。 4. The shelter was proof against the bitter weather. 这个棚子可以避寒。 5. It is part of your duty to proof twenty pages. 校对20页是你分内之事。', '名词: proofer 过去式: proofed 过去分词: proofed 现在分词: proofing 第三人称单数: proofs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('radio', '[\'reɪdioʊ]', 'n.收音机；无线电 v.用无线电通讯', '1. I\'m afraid this old radio is beyond repair. 恐怕这台旧收音机不能修了。 2. Radio reception isn\'t very good here. 这里的无线电接收情况不太好。 3. Every ship is required to radio its position. 要求每一艘船用无线电报告各自所在的位置。', '名词复数: radios 过去式: radioed 过去分词: radioed 现在分词: radioing 第三人称单数: radios');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('geology', '[dʒi\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.地质学；（某地区的）地质情况；地质学的著作', '1. I know only a few streaks about geology. 我对地质学只是略知一二。 2. Geology is the science of the earth\'s history. 地质学是研究地球历史的科学。 3. The students went to study the geology of that region. 学生们去研究那个地区的地质情况。 4. It\'s essentially a mimic of the natural process of geology on a smaller time scale. 它实际上是对地质情况自然过程的一个模拟，只是时间更短。', '形容词: geologic 副词: geologically 名词: geologist 名词复数: geologies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arise', '[ə\'raɪz]', 'vi.出现；升起；上升；发生；起来', '1. An opportunity has arisen. 机会来了。 2. Tell our comrades to keep calm when problems arise. 告诉同志们遇事要沉着。 3. Notice what emotions arise within you. 注意到在你内心升起的情绪。 4. Whatever it is, let it arise and look at it mindfully. 无论是什么，让它升起，觉知的观察它。', '过去式: arose 过去分词: arisen 现在分词: arising 第三人称单数: arises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stern', '[stɜːrn]', 'adj.严厉的；严峻的；苛刻的；坚决的 n.尾部；船尾', '1. He received a stern rebuke from his superior. 他受到上司的严厉斥责。 2. She had a stern father who never praised her. 她父亲很严厉，他从来没有表扬过她。 3. The teacher\'s stern look reduced him to silence. 教师神情严肃，他便静了下来。 4. He came close to the painter and looked steadfastly into his stern eyes. 他走近画家,并且死死地盯着他那目光严峻的眼睛。 5. Move your stern, I want to sit down. 你把屁股挪一挪，我想坐下。', '副词: sternly 比较级: sterner 最高级: sternest 名词: sternness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('maintain', '[meɪn\'teɪn]', 'vt.维持；维修；保养；坚持；断言', '1. It is absolutely vital that food supplies should be maintained. 维持食物的供给是绝对必要的。 2. They also help us to maintain the machinery. 他们还帮助我们维修机器。 3. They tell the peasants in detail how to maintain the pumps. 他们详细地教给农民怎样保养抽水机。 4. It is clearly illogical to maintain such a proposition. 坚持这种主张显然是没有道理的。', '形容词: maintainable 名词: maintainability 过去式: maintained 过去分词: maintained 现在分词: maintaining 第三人称单数: maintains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('revolution', '[ˌrevə\'luːʃn]', 'n.革命；变革；重大改变；旋转', '1. Most countries have had revolutions aganist the government. 大多数国家发生过反对政府的革命。 2. The industrial revolution had taken place in England first. 工业革命首先在英国发生。 3. Those people go around preaching revolution. 那些人到处宣扬革命。 4. The invention of aircraft caused a revolution in our ways of travelling. 飞机的发明引起了旅行方式的巨大改变。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trumpet', '[\'trʌmpɪt]', 'n.喇叭；喇叭声；喇叭手 vt.宣扬；鼓吹；吹嘘 vi.吹喇叭；发出喇叭似的声音', '1. The trumpet sounded. 喇叭吹响了。 2. He plays the violin, but I play the trumpet. 他拉提琴，我吹喇叭。 3. Now the dog is singing with the trumpet. 现在这只狗正在合着喇叭唱歌。 4. A blast of the trumpet gave her a start. 突然发出的喇叭声吓了她一跳。 5. He likes to trumpet his own opinions. 他喜欢宣扬自己的意见。 6. The boy is trumpeting. 这个小男孩正在吹喇叭。', '过去式: trumpeted 过去分词: trumpeted 现在分词: trumpeting 第三人称单数: trumpets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deteriorate', '[dɪ\'tɪriəreɪt]', 'v.恶化；变质；衰退', '1. We cannot allow the situation to deteriorate. 我们不容许情况恶化。 2. Relation between the two countries have deteriorated sharply in recent week. 最近几周那两个国家间的关系严重恶化了。 3. Food is apt to deteriorate in summer. 食物在夏天容易变质。 4. The discussion deteriorated into a bitter quarrel. 这场讨论演变成了激烈的争吵。', '形容词: deteriorative 名词: deterioration 过去式: deteriorated 过去分词: deteriorated 现在分词: deteriorating 第三人称单数: deteriorates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nuclear', '[\'nuːkliər]', 'adj.原子核的；原子能的；核心的', '1. Nuclear binding energies are strikingly high. 原子核的结合能是极大的。 2. The college students are active to crusade against the nuclear weapons. 大学生们积极投入开展反对核武器的运 动。 3. They decided to establish a nuclear power station. 他们决定修建一所核电站。 4. A nuclear family consists of parents and their children only. 核心家庭一般只有父母和孩子两代。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fiction', '[\'fɪkʃn]', 'n.小说；虚构；杜撰', '1. Real life is sometimes stranger than fiction. 现实生活有时比小说还离奇。 2. I like to read science fiction. 我喜欢读科幻小说。 3. It\'s important to distinguish fact from fiction. 把现实与虚构区分开来是很重要的。 4. His testimony is a complete fiction. 他的证言全是虚构。', '形容词: fictional 副词: fictionally 名词: fictionality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shell', '[ʃel]', 'n.壳；炮弹；[计]外壳程序 v.脱落；去壳；拾贝壳；炮轰', '1. There is an ornament made of shells on the wall. 墙上有一个贝壳做成的装饰品。 2. All that remained of the building after the fire was an empty shell. 一场大火过后，这座建筑剩下的只是一个空壳。 3. The snail retreated into its shell. 蜗牛缩进壳里去了。 4. Shells were bursting all around. 炮弹在四处爆炸。 5. The wheat will shell after a few days. 麦子已熟透，再过几天就会脱落了。', '名词: sheller 过去式: shelled 过去分词: shelled 现在分词: shelling 第三人称单数: shells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tree', '[triː]', 'n.树；树状物', '1. We plant trees and flowers in spring. 我们在春天种花种树。 2. In the storm I took shelter under the tree. 暴风雨时，我正在树下躲避。 3. She sat very still under the tree. 她在树底下静静地坐着。 4. Dates showered down when we shook the tree. 我们摇树时，枣子纷纷落下。', '形容词: treeless 过去式: treed 过去分词: treed 现在分词: treeing 第三人称单数: trees');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spy', '[spaɪ]', 'n.间谍；侦探；侦察 v.侦探；监视；看到；找出', '1. The spy was expelled from the realm. 这名间谍被驱逐出境。 2. This evidence reinforces my view that he is a spy. 这个证据证实了我认为他是间谍的这一看法。 3. The scout was sent to spy out the land. 侦探被派出去秘密侦察高地去了。 4. She hired a detective to spy on her husband. 她雇了一个侦探来监视她丈夫。 5. The scout was sent to spy out the land. 侦探被派出去秘密侦察高地去了。', '名词复数: spies 过去式: spied 过去分词: spied 现在分词: spying 第三人称单数: spies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slap', '[slæp]', 'n.侮辱；掴；拍击声 vt.侮辱；拍击；惩罚；申斥 adv.直接地；正面地；突然地', '1. It is a slap in the fame to call me a\'fat pig\'. 叫我“胖猪”是对我的侮辱。 2. It is a bit of a slap in the face when she refuseed to see me. 她拒绝见我，这简直是侮辱我。 3. He gave her a slap on the cheek and she began to cry. 他打了她一耳光，她就哭起来了。 4. He hit the water with a resounding slap. 他啪的一声拍了一下水。 5. You were slapping me just now. 你刚才正在侮辱我。 6. The thief ran slap into a policeman. 那贼与警察撞了一个满怀。', '名词: slapper 过去式: slapped 过去分词: slapped 现在分词: slapping 第三人称单数: slaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invest', '[ɪn\'vest]', 'v.投资；投入', '1. I won\'t invest my money in his company. 我不会把我的钱投资到他的公司。 2. I\'d like to invest some money in real estate. 我想在地产上投资点钱。 3. They intended to invest hugely in new technology. 他们打算在新技术方面投入大量资金。 4. Everyone should invest some time in community service. 每个人都应该花些时间在社区服务上。', '形容词: investable 名词: investor 过去式: invested 过去分词: invested 现在分词: investing 第三人称单数: invests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sometimes', '[\'sʌmtaɪmz]', 'adv.有时；间或', '1. Old people are sometimes forgetful. 老人有时爱忘事。 2. Sometimes the patient cried for the pain. 有时这个病人疼得哭起来。 3. Love is sometimes put in range with a career. 人们往往认为爱情和事业是并驾齐驱的。 4. Sometimes she saw the flash of a torch through a chink in the curtains. 她间或透过窗帘的缝隙能瞥见手电筒的闪光。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recollect', '[ˌrekə\'lekt]', 'v.回忆；回想；记起', '1. She can recollect meeting the king. 她能回忆起觐见国王的事. 2. He is able to clearly recollect her looking. 他可以很清楚地回忆起她的容貌. 3. I recollect the days passed by the seaside. 我回想起了当初在海边度过的日子。 4. I don\'t recollect having seen her before. 我记不起来以前曾见到过她。', '形容词: recollective 副词: recollectively 过去式: recollected 过去分词: recollected 现在分词: recollecting 第三人称单数: recollects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('entrepreneur', '[ˌɑːntrəprə\'nɜːr]', 'n.企业家；承包商；主办者', '1. He is a shipping entrepreneur. 他是个航运企业家。 2. The entrepreneur has become a news figure. 这位企业家变成了新闻人物。', '形容词: entrepreneurial 名词: entrepreneurialism');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('August', '[\'ɔːɡəst]', 'adj.（a~）威严的；尊贵的 n.八月', '1. There\'s an august group of statesmen in the auditorium. 大礼堂里坐着一群德高望重的政治家。 2. The august presence of the queen impressed me. 皇后尊贵的出场给我留下了深刻印象。 3. Tourism is at its peak in August. 旅游业在八月份达到高峰。 4. His summer vacation will end in the late August. 他的暑假将于八月底结束。', '副词: augustly 名词: augustness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('moan', '[moʊn]', 'n.呻吟声；抱怨声 vt.抱怨；呻吟 vi.呻吟；抱怨', '1. Each time she moved her head she let out a moan. 她每转动一下头，就发出一声呻吟。 2. A moan escaped the badly wounded soldier. 那个重伤员不禁呻吟了一声。 3. His constant moan is that no one understands him. 他老是抱怨没有人理解他。 4. She moaned her misfortunes to anyone who would listen. 她向任何乐于听的人哀叹命运不济。 5. Suddenly he began to moan in his sleep. 突然他在睡梦中开始呻吟。', '过去式: moaned 过去分词: moaned 现在分词: moaning 第三人称单数: moans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dread', '[dred]', 'v.惧怕；担心 n.恐惧；可怕的人或事 adj.恐怖的；使人敬畏的', '1. I dread having to visit the dentist . 我害怕看牙医。 2. I dread to think what will happen if she finds out the truth. 我不敢去想她知道真相后会怎么样。 3. Much of what we dread is really due to indistinctness of outline. 畏生于不明，大抵如此。 4. The Jews lived in dread of being caught. 这些犹太人生活在会遭到拘捕的恐惧之中。 5. The countryside lay as under some dread enchantment. 乡村好像躺在某种可怖的魔法之下。', '过去式: dreaded 过去分词: dreaded 现在分词: dreading 第三人称单数: dreads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aggravate', '[\'æɡrəveɪt]', 'vt.恶化；严重', '1. Scratching can aggravate the rash. 搔痒会使疹子发炎。 2. The Europeans\' appeasement policy towards irrational regimes would only aggravate the hidden dangers. 欧洲国家对非理性政权的绥靖政策,只会让潜在危机恶化。 3. This will aggravate the current scarcity of natural resources caused by environmental degradation. 这将会加剧由环境恶化而导致的自然资源匮乏的情况。 4. The lack of rain aggravated the already serious shortage of food. 干旱少雨使原本就很严重的粮食短缺问题更加严重。', '形容词: aggravative 副词: aggravatingly 名词: aggravator 过去式: aggravated 过去分词: aggravated 现在分词: aggravating 第三人称单数: aggravates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('partly', '[\'pɑːrtli]', 'adv.在一定程度上；部分地；不完全地', '1. You have introduced a partly random component. 你介绍了一个在一定程度上属于偶然的成分。 2. The transformation is partly due to demographics. 这一变化一定程度上是源于人口的变化。 3. Their energy is partly dissipated. 它们的能量被部分地消耗掉。 4. This partly accounts for the efficiency of the company. 这部分地说明了公司效率高的原因。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('decline', '[dɪ\'klaɪn]', 'v.下降；减少；变弱；拒绝；倾斜 n.衰微；跌落；晚年', '1. I wish prices would decline. 但愿物价下降。 2. The price of 14 inches TV set declined from 400 to 320 yuan each. 14英寸的电视机每台从400元降到320元。 3. He spent his declining years in the country. 他在乡间度过晚年。 4. I must regretfully decline your kind invitation. 我很抱歉必须拒绝你的盛情邀请。 5. This decline in vigour with the passing of time is called ageing. 这种随着时间流逝的活力衰退就叫做衰老。', '形容词: declinable 名词: decliner 过去式: declined 过去分词: declined 现在分词: declining 第三人称单数: declines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('automation', '[ˌɔːtə\'meɪʃn]', 'n.自动化', '1. Automation has obsoleted many unskilled workers. 自动化使很多非技术工人受到淘汰。 2. So is the case with industrial automation. 在工业自动化方面，情况也一样。', '形容词: automative');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gradual', '[\'ɡrædʒuəl]', 'adj.逐渐的；逐步的；平缓的', '1. This leads to gradual memory exhaustion. 这将导致存储空间逐渐的耗尽。 2. There has been a gradual increase in the number of people owning cars. 拥有汽车的人数一直在逐渐上升。 3. I advocate a policy of gradual reform. 我拥护逐步改革的政策。 4. Gradual change is preferable to sudden, large- scale change. 逐步的变化比突然的、大规模的变化更好。', '副词: gradually 名词: gradualness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('entrance', '[\'entrəns]', 'n.入口；进入；登场；进入权 vt.使入迷；使狂喜', '1. There is an entrance just around the corner. 拐角处有个入口。 2. I\'ll meet you at the entrance of the zoo tomorrow. 明天我会在动物园的入口处和你见面。 3. A lighthouse marks the entrance to the harbour. 灯塔是进入海港航道的标志。 4. The actress makes her entrance in Act 3. 女演员在第三幕登场。 5. Her beauty entirely entrances him. 她的美丽完全使他入迷了。', '副词: entrancingly 名词: entrancement 过去式: entranced 过去分词: entranced 现在分词: entrancing 第三人称单数: entrances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cloud', '[klaʊd]', 'n.云；阴影', '1. A cloud is a mass of vapor in the sky. 云是天空中的水汽团。 2. When there are black clouds you can tell it\'s going to rain. 有乌云的时候，就知道快下雨了。 3. His sudden departure cast a cloud upon our scheme. 他的突然离去给我们的计划投下一层阴影。 4. The sad news of her father\'s death was the only cloud on an otherwise happy year. 她父亲的死讯是她愉快的一年中唯一伤心的事。', '形容词: cloudless 过去式: clouded 过去分词: clouded 现在分词: clouding 第三人称单数: clouds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('auction', '[\'ɔːkʃn]', 'n.拍卖 vt.拍卖', '1. We will put the car up for auction. 我们将把这辆小车拍卖。 2. The picture should fetch 2000 pounds at auction. 这张画拍卖可得2000英镑。 3. We had a private view of the jewels before the public auction. 那些珠宝公开拍卖以前我们私下看了预展。 4. They will auction off a collection of oils. 他们将拍卖一批收藏的油画。', '过去式: auctioned 过去分词: auctioned 现在分词: auctioning 第三人称单数: auctions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gay', '[ɡeɪ]', 'n.同性恋(多指男同性恋） adj.快乐的；鲜艳的；放荡的；同性恋的', '1. They object to the movie\'s depiction of gay people. 他们反对这部影片对同性恋者的刻画。 2. She gave a gay laugh. 她发出了快活的笑声。 3. The package was tied with gay ribbons. 包裹用色彩鲜艳的丝带捆扎好。 4. They painted the room in gay colours. 他们用鲜艳的颜色粉刷房间。', '比较级: gayer 最高级: gayest 名词: gayness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acknowledge', '[ək\'nɑːlɪdʒ]', 'vt.承认；告知收到；公认；表示感谢；注意到', '1. We acknowledged the need for reform. 我们承认改革的需要。 2. Please acknowledge this cheque as soon as you receive it. 收到该支票后,请立即告知。 3. We hope you can acknowledge your mistake in public. 希望你当众认错。 4. We are sending you some money in acknowledgement of your valuable help. 我们送些酬劳，对您的大力协助聊表谢意。', '形容词: acknowledgeable 过去式: acknowledged 过去分词: acknowledged 现在分词: acknowledging 第三人称单数: acknowledges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('those', '[ðoʊz]', 'pron.那些 adj.那些', '1. Successful are those who are willing to take pains. 成功的人都是那些肯努力的人。 2. The oranges in the box are better than those on the shelf. 箱子的橙子比橱上的那些好。 3. Let\'s forget about those worries. 咱们忘掉那些烦恼的事吧。 4. It\'s time to put away those foolish ideas. 是该放弃那些愚蠢的想法了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('regard', '[rɪ\'ɡɑːrd]', 'v.尊敬；视为；注视；留意；和 ... 有关 n.关心；尊敬；注意；致意；考虑', '1. The artist was highly regarded. 这位艺术家非常受尊敬。 2. I regard reading as a form of recreation. 我把看书当作一种消遣的形式。 3. He regards the bad weather as a prognostic of failure. 他将坏天气视为失败的预兆。 4. He regarded the famous scientist with worship in his eyes. 他以敬慕的目光注视着这位著名科学家。 5. No one showed the least regard for his feelings. 根本没有人关心他的感受。', '过去式: regarded 过去分词: regarded 现在分词: regarding 第三人称单数: regards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fence', '[fens]', 'n.栅栏；围墙；买卖赃物的人 v.用篱笆围住；束缚；击剑；回避', '1. He tried to see over the fence but it was too high. 他试图从栅栏上面看过去，但它太高了。 2. He hired a workman to repair the fence. 他雇用了一个工人修理围墙。 3. That fence is the limit of the schoolyard. 那堵围墙是校园的界限。 4. The loot had disappeared and been handled by a fence. 赃物失踪后被一个销脏的人处理掉了。 5. One end of the garden was fenced off for chickens. 花园的一端已用篱笆隔开来养鸡。', '名词: fencer 过去式: fenced 过去分词: fenced 现在分词: fencing 第三人称单数: fences');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stomach', '[\'stʌmək]', 'n.胃；胃口；腹部 vt.忍受；吃得下', '1. He had had too much to eat and his stomach started to kick up. 他吃得太多了,胃不舒服。 2. Anxiety may disorder the stomach. 忧虑可能会引起胃部不适。 3. The stomach revolts at such food. 这样的食物倒胃囗。 4. The film about eye operations turned my stomach. 这部眼科手术的影片看得我恶心极了。 5. I can\'t stomach your constant nagging. 我再也忍受不了你不停的唠叨了。', '过去式: stomached 过去分词: stomached 现在分词: stomaching 第三人称单数: stomachs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tanker', '[\'tæŋkər]', 'n.油轮；加油飞机；罐车', '1. The tanker sank and pollute the sea. 油轮沉没了，污染了海水。 2. The ship sank through a collision with an oil tanker. 这条船因与油轮相撞而沉没。 3. These planes can be refueled in the air by tanker. 这些飞机可在空中接受加油。 4. The driver of the fuel tanker crashed to avoid a car. 该燃油罐车的司机为躲避一辆汽车翻车了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('least', '[liːst]', 'adj.最小的；最少的 adv.最小地；最少地；最轻微地 n.最小；最少', '1. The least noise would startle the timid child. 最小的响声也会吓着这个胆小的孩子的。 2. The greatest talkers are always the least doers. 大言不惭的总是做得最少的人。 3. She came when we least expected her. 她在我们最意料不到的时候来了。 4. He worked hardest but was paid least. 他工作最辛苦，但所得报酬却最少。 5. He was the one who did the least of the work and got the most of the money. 他就是那个做活最少而拿钱最多的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('neglect', '[nɪ\'ɡlekt]', 'vt.忽略；忽视；疏忽 n.疏忽；忽视', '1. You shouldn\'t neglect your health. 你不该忽略你的健康。 2. No country can afford to neglect education. 任何国家都不容忽视教育。 3. He neglected to write and say \"Thank you\". 他忘了写信道谢。 4. She was severely criticized for neglect of duty. 她因玩忽职守而受到严厉批评。', '名词: neglecter 过去式: neglected 过去分词: neglected 现在分词: neglecting 第三人称单数: neglects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('harness', '[\'hɑːrnɪs]', 'n.马具；安全带；甲胄；系在身上的绳子 vt.束以马具；披上甲胄；利用；管理；控制', '1. Stirrup is an important part of harness. 马镫是马具的一个重要的部分。 2. You can not judge of the horse by the harness. 凭马具难断马优劣。 3. Safety harness is quite necessary in terms of the accidents. 考虑到意外事故,安全带是必要的。 4. The parachutist was buckled into his harness. 跳伞者扣上了背带。 5. I harness the horse to the cart. 我把马套在车上。', '名词: harnesser 过去式: harnessed 过去分词: harnessed 现在分词: harnessing 第三人称单数: harnesses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('volcano', '[vɑːl\'keɪnoʊ]', 'n.火山', '1. Vesuvius is an active volcano. 维苏威山是一座活火山。 2. The eruption of volcano makes many people lose their lives. 火山的爆发使许多人丧失了生命。 3. That volcano cast forth lots of lava and ashes. 那火山喷了出大量熔岩和灰烬。 4. The erupting volcano was an awe-inspiring sight. 火山爆发是使人畏惧的景象。', '名词复数: volcanoes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mayor', '[\'meɪər]', 'n.市长', '1. The mayor made a speech at the opening. 市长在开幕式上发表了演说。 2. The mayor is determined to clean up the city. 市长决心清除市内的不良现象。 3. He is the deputy mayor of the city. 他是本市的副市长。', '形容词: mayoral 名词: mayorship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('edible', '[\'edəbl]', 'adj.可食用的 n.食品；食物', '1. Is linseed oil edible? 亚麻籽油可以食用吗？ 2. Some of the algae are edible. 有些藻类是可以吃的。 3. Throw that tainted meat away; it\'s not edible. 把那块腐烂的肉扔掉，不能再吃了。 4. This food is scarcely edible. 这种食物真是难以下咽。 5. I eat everything that is edible. 我吃食品的每件事物。', '名词: edibility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('believe', '[bɪ\'liːv]', 'v.相信；认为', '1. We believe in his ability. 我们相信他的才干。 2. Some people believe in God and others don\'t. 有人相信上帝; 有人则不相信。 3. Some people believe poverty engenders crime. 有人认为贫困生罪恶。 4. They believe it is essential to defy convention. 他们认为反抗流俗是绝对必要的。', '名词: believer 过去式: believed 过去分词: believed 现在分词: believing 第三人称单数: believes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appal', '[ə\'pɔːl]', 'v.使 ... 惊骇；使 ... 吓坏；<古>削弱；失败', '1. We were appalled when we heard that the chairman had been murdered. 听说主席被谋杀，我们都吓坏了。 2. The prospect of another war appalled us. 想到有可能发生另一场战争，我们不寒而栗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hurricane', '[\'hɜːrəkən]', 'n.飓风；暴风', '1. The hurricane destroyed the whole village. 飓风把整个村子都毁掉了。 2. The hurricane screamed outside. 外面飓风呼啸著。 3. The hurricane has a speed of 73 miles per hour. 飓风每小时73英里。 4. The radio alerted the citizens to prepare for the hurricane. 电台警告市民们作好预防暴风准备。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('calendar', '[\'kælɪndər]', 'n.日历；历法；日程表；一览表 vt.把 ... 列入日程表', '1. He tore a leaf from the calendar. 他从日历上撕下一页。 2. The other is the haab, or Calendar Round. 另外一个称为哈伯历，或者是历法圆周。 3. But this calendar also had problems. 可是这种历法也有问题。 4. I don\'t see how we can fit this into the mayor\'s busy calendar. 我不明白我们要怎样把这件事挤进市长满满的日程表中。 5. The assistant will calendar the next appointment in for me. 助手会把下一个会面排进我的日程表。', '过去式: calendared 过去分词: calendared 现在分词: calendaring 第三人称单数: calendars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clue', '[kluː]', 'n.线索；提示', '1. There is no clue to the identity of the thief. 没有确定窃贼身分的线索。 2. We have no clue as to where she went after she left home. 我们对她离家後去往何处毫无线索。 3. They are now trying to chase down all possible clues. 他们现在正在设法寻找一切可能的线索。 4. I gave him another clue, but he still didn\'t twig (the answer). 我又提示他一次，他还是不理解(那答案).', '过去式: clued 过去分词: clued 现在分词: clueing/cluing 第三人称单数: clues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('national', '[\'næʃnəl]', 'adj.民族的；国家的；全国性的；国立的；国有的 n.国民 （复）nationals: 全国性比赛.', '1. These ancient buildings are part of the national heritage. 这些古建是民族遗产的一部分。 2. We must safeguard our national interests. 我们必须保卫国家的利益。 3. National wealth depends to a high degree on a country\'s educational standard. 国民财富在很大程度上取决于一个国家的教育水准。 4. Our newspaper is a national newspaper. 我们的报纸是全国性的报纸。 5. He\'s a French national working in Italy. 他是在意大利工作的法国人。', '副词: nationally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('correspondent', '[ˌkɔːrə\'spɑːndənt]', 'n.通讯记者；通信者 adj.与 ... 一致的；相应的', '1. The newspaper has a foreign correspondent. 这家报纸有个外国通讯记者。 2. A good correspondent does not procrastinate. 一位勤于写信的通信者不会拖延。 3. You know what a poor correspondent I am. 你知道我是一个多么懒于写信的人。 4. The result was correspondent with my wishes. 结果与我的愿望是一致的。', '副词: correspondently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('afterward', '[\'ɑːftəwəd]', 'adv.后来；以后', '1. The couple lived happily ever afterward. 这对夫妇后来快乐地生活着。 2. Afterward, he once had held the post of the Lucar palace musician. 后来，他曾担任过卢卡宫廷乐师。 3. Lying awake long afterward, my words haunted me. 直到很久以后，我还是常想起我的那些话。 4. Santino would have sulked and behaved badly for weeks afterward. 桑蒂诺会生闷气，并且以后几个星期表现不好。', '异体字: afterwards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('zigzag', '[\'zɪɡzæɡ]', 'n.曲折；之字形 adj.曲折的；锯齿形的 adv.曲折地；成锯齿形地 vt.使曲折 vi.曲折前行', '1. As long as the insect remains in the odor stream, fairly direct or weakly zigzag flight paths are maintained until it overshoots the odor source. 只要昆虫与气味一接触时，它们沿着几乎是直接的或稍有曲折的飞行路线，直到越过气味源。 2. The same effect causes student drivers to zigzag down the road, as each late large correction of the steering wheel overreacts to the last late overcorrection. 这就跟新手开车总是开出之字形道理一样，因为每次转动方向盘，总是会矫枉过正，超过上次校正所偏离的部分。 3. As long as the insect remains in the odor stream, fairly direct or weakly zigzag flight paths are maintained until it overshoots the odor source. 只要昆虫与气味一接触时，它们沿着几乎是直接的或稍有曲折的飞行路线，直到越过气味源。', '过去式: zigzagged 过去分词: zigzagged 现在分词: zigzagging 第三人称单数: zigzags');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outset', '[\'aʊtset]', 'n.开始；开端', '1. At the outset, it looked like a nice day. 开始的时候，天看上去很晴朗。 2. You should explain this to him from the outset. 你应该一开始就向他解释这事。 3. An ardent outset may be followed by declension. 热情的开端可能继之以冷漠。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('joint', '[dʒɔɪnt]', 'adj.联合的；共同的；连带的；合资的 n.关节；接头；接合处；接缝；夜总会 v.贴合；连接', '1. They covenanted with us for establishing a joint venture. 他们就建立合资公司的事和我们签了合约。 2. In this contract, Board shall mean the board of director of the joint venture . 在本合同中，board指的是本合资企业的董事会。 3. These foreigners have put forward a proposal for a joint venture. 这些外国人提出了一个合资企业的建议。 4. The joint isn\'t quite done yet. 这一大块肉煮得不太熟。 5. Does any one know who can joint sales calls? 谁知道谁可以做联合销售拜访?', '过去式: jointed 过去分词: jointed 现在分词: jointing 第三人称单数: joints');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peculiar', '[pɪ\'kjuːliər]', 'adj.奇怪的；特殊的；独特的；古怪的 n.特权', '1. Did you notice anything peculiar? 你注意到有什么异常的事吗？ 2. The food has a peculiar taste. 这食物有种怪味道。 3. A peculiar feeling came over Feliks. 一种特殊的情感传遍费利克斯全身。 4. This actor has a peculiar charm, which attracts middle-aged women. 这个演员有种特殊的魅力，吸引了很多中年女性。 5. It\'s the manager\'s peculiar to use this meeting room. 使用这间会议室是经理的特权。', '副词: peculiarly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('critic', '[\'krɪtɪk]', 'n.评论家；批评家', '1. She is a very discerning art critic. 她是位眼光敏锐的艺术评论家。 2. He has a reputation for being a forthright critic. 他是以直率著称的评论家。 3. Have you read the article written by that famous critic? 你读过那个著名的批评家写的这篇文章吗？ 4. A critic is a man whose watch is five minutes ahead of other people\'s watch. 批评家，是一个他的表要比别人的表快上五分钟的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tough', '[tʌf]', 'adj.强硬的；棘手的，难办的；艰苦的；严厉的；牢固的，强壮的；坚强的，坚韧的 adv.以强硬的态度；强硬地，顽强地 n.暴徒; 恶棍', '1. The government is taking a tough line on drug abuse. 政府对滥用麻醉药品采取强硬方针。 2. I am well aware that this is a tough job. 我深知这是一件棘手的工作。 3. Conditions are rather tough here. 这里条件比较艰苦。 4. The law is tough on offenders. 该法律对违法者处罚很严厉。 5. A gang of toughs attacked the police. 一群暴徒袭击了警察。', '副词: toughly 比较级: tougher 最高级: toughest 名词: toughness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ancestor', '[\'ænsestər]', 'n.祖宗；祖先；原种', '1. During the festival the investor investigated his ancestor. 节日期间投资者调查了他的祖宗。 2. They said their ancestor was a famous hunter and a crack hunter. 他们说他们的祖宗是个有名的猎人，也是个神枪手。 3. People who share an ancestor are called relatives. 有同一个祖先的叫做亲戚。 4. She has worshipped her ancestor. 她已拜过她的祖先。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('her', '[hər]', 'pron.她(宾格) adj.她的 abbr.纹章术；纹章学(=heraldry)', '1. That\'s her book. 那是她的书。 2. Give her the book. 把这本书给她。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('murder', '[\'mɜːrdər]', 'n.谋杀；谋杀案；<俚>要命的事 vt.谋杀；糟蹋；损坏 vi.谋杀', '1. He did a long stretch for attempted murder. 他因谋杀未遂罪坐了很长时间的牢。 2. The law arrived on the scene of murder. 警察来到谋杀现场。 3. There have been several murders this year. 今年发生了好几起谋杀案。 4. The murder trial lasted six weeks. 法庭对这一谋杀案的审理为时六周。 5. His parents and sister were all murdered by the terrorists. 他的父母和姐姐都是被恐怖分子杀害的。 6. The law arrived on the scene of murder. 警察来到谋杀现场。', '名词: murderer 过去式: murdered 过去分词: murdered 现在分词: murdering 第三人称单数: murders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('greeting', '[\'ɡriːtɪŋ]', 'n.问候；打招呼', '1. \"How are you?\" is a conventional greeting. “你好”是一个习惯问候语。 2. Her greeting was cold and strained. 她的问候冷淡而勉强。 3. He acknowledged the greeting with a nod. 他点一点头，回答了对他的问候。 4. He gave us a cheery greeting. 他愉快地跟我们打招呼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('progressive', '[prə\'ɡresɪv]', 'adj.先进的；前进的；渐进的；革新的(音乐上的） n.进步分子；革新主义者', '1. She is the most progressive writer of that times. 她是那个时代最进步的作家。 2. That famous progressive thinker was asked to deliver a speech at the meeting. 那位著名的进步思想家被邀请在会议上发表演讲。 3. History can not hold progressive movement. 历史无法阻挡前进的步伐。 4. He noted a progressive speech impediment. 他发觉，说话障碍逐渐厉害起来。 5. The butchers at Pingkiang killed progressive people. 平江惨案的那些刽子手，他们把进步分子杀了。', '副词: progressively 名词: progressiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('survey', '[\'sɜːrveɪ]', 'n.问卷；测量；调查；纵览；视察 v.调查；审视；研究；测量；勘定；环视', '1. A recent survey of public opinions shows that most people are worried about the increasing crime. 一份最近的民意调查表明,大多数人对不断增长的犯罪率表示忧虑。 2. The surveyor made a survey of the land. 测量员对土地进行了测量。 3. After much delay, the results of the survey were published. 耽搁多时之后,调查结果终于公布了。 4. From the top of the hill you can have a survey of the whole city. 从山顶上你可以俯瞰整个城市。 5. They surveyed the damage inflicted by the storm. 他们调查了暴风雨造成的损失。', '名词: surveyor 名词复数: surveys 过去式: surveyed 过去分词: surveyed 现在分词: surveying 第三人称单数: surveys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('proportion', '[prə\'pɔːrʃn]', 'n.部分；比例；均衡；（复）规模 vt.使成比例；使均衡；分摊', '1. A large proportion of my time is spent in studying. 我的大部分时间花在学习上。 2. This door is narrow in proportion to its height. 这扇门就其高度的比例而言窄了些。 3. The two windows are in admirable proportion. 这两扇窗户十分相称. 4. The tree can grow to massive proportions. 这课树可以长到很大。 5. We must proportion the punishment to the crime . 我们必须使刑罚与罪行相当。', '形容词: proportionable 副词: proportionably 名词: proportioner 过去式: proportioned 过去分词: proportioned 现在分词: proportioning 第三人称单数: proportions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stack', '[stæk]', 'n.堆；一大堆；【计】存储栈；迭式存储器，栈式存储器；存储栈数据 v.堆积；堆放', '1. The grain has gone mouldy in the stack. 垛里的谷子发霉了。 2. He placed his books in a neat stack. 他把书整整齐齐放成一堆。 3. I\'ve got stacks of work to do. 我有一大堆活儿要做。 4. There is a stack of dishes to be washed in the kitchen. 厨房里还有一大堆盘子要洗。 5. Please stack the materials up here. 请把材料堆在这里。', '形容词: stackable 名词: stacker 过去式: stacked 过去分词: stacked 现在分词: stacking 第三人称单数: stacks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('statute', '[\'stætʃuːt]', 'n.法令；法规；条例', '1. Working hours are limited by statute. 工作时间有法令限制。 2. The sole purpose of this statute is to promote mining. 这项法令的唯一目的就是要促进矿业开采。 3. We must obey the statutes in this country. 我们必须遵守这个国家的法规。 4. Penalties are laid down in the statute. 法规中有关于惩罚措施的规定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('battery', '[\'bætəri]', 'n.电池；一系列；炮兵连；排炮；[律]殴打', '1. They are electrifying the battery. 他们正给电池充电。 2. My car battery has run down; it needs recharging. 我的汽车电池没电了，需要充电。 3. We would undergo a battery of tests. 我们要进行一系列试验。 4. A captain commands a company or battery. 一个上尉指挥一个连队或炮兵连。', '名词复数: batteries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('persuade', '[pər\'sweɪd]', 'vt.说服；劝说', '1. How can I persuade you of my sincerity? 我如何能够让你相信我的诚意？ 2. We are persuaded of the justice of her case. 我们确信对她案件的审理是公正的。 3. I am not fully persuaded by the evidence. 这证据不足以使我充分信服。 4. You try and persuade her (to come out with us). 你去试试劝她(跟我们一起出去)吧。', '形容词: persuadable 名词: persuader 过去式: persuaded 过去分词: persuaded 现在分词: persuading 第三人称单数: persuades');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('zero', '[\'zɪroʊ]', 'n.零；零度；最低点；完全没有；无足轻重的人或物 adj.零的；无价值的；零视度的 v.把 ... 调零；瞄准；集中注意；迫近', '1. Make sure you are not dividing by zero. 确保不会除零。 2. It was five below zero last night. 昨夜温度是零下五度。 3. The temperature will be above zero. 气温将在零度以上。 4. The reputation of the conjurer was rapidly sinking below zero. 魔术师的信誉一下子下降到最低点。 5. The probability of a peace agreement being reached is zero. 达成和平协定的概率是零。 6. He is well-known for his capability to zero out taxes for his clients. 他以能够为客户合法避税出名。', '名词复数: zeros 过去式: zeroed 过去分词: zeroed 现在分词: zeroing 第三人称单数: zeroes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('badminton', '[\'bædmɪntən]', 'n.羽毛球', '1. I like to play badminton in my spare time. 我喜欢在闲暇时打羽毛球。 2. He went to the badminton club at times during his school days. 他上学时有时到羽毛球俱乐部去。 3. He\'s in his element when playing badminton. 他打起羽毛球来真是得心应手。 4. He plays tennis better than badminton. 他网球比羽毛球打得好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remnant', '[\'remnənt]', 'n.残余；残剩余；残存者；零头 adj.剩余的', '1. If something has been partly used or destroyed, we use remains or remnants. 若某物的一部分已用掉或毁掉，其剩余或残存部分可用。 2. I will sell this remnant to you, at cost. 我愿将此剩货照成本卖给你。 3. The remnants of last night\'s meal were still on the table. 昨天晚上的剩余物还在桌子上。 4. The Ainu settlers in Hokkaido are the last remnant of a prehistoric race. 北海道的阿伊努人是史前某个种族的最后残存者。 5. The beautiful curtain is made of remnant materials. 这个漂亮的窗帘是用零头布做的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('caution', '[\'kɔːʃn]', 'n.警告；慎重；戒备；吸引人眼球的人或物 vt.警告；劝告', '1. The teacher gave Tom a caution and told him never to do it again. 老师给了汤姆一次警告,叫他不许再那样做。 2. He told us to proceed with caution. 他要我们谨慎行事。 3. Always he sought someone to whom he could talk without caution. 他一直在找一个能够随便谈谈的人。 4. I must caution you against the danger. 我必须告诫你应谨防危险。', '过去式: cautioned 过去分词: cautioned 现在分词: cautioning 第三人称单数: cautions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('store', '[stɔːr]', 'n.商店；贮藏；充裕 vt.储存；贮藏；保存', '1. The fire was so damaging that the store had to close its doors. 火灾造成的损失太严重， 这个商店不得不停业。 2. He always keeps several cases of wine in store. 他总是备有几箱酒。 3. She has acquired such a vast store of knowledge. 她的知识面非常广。 4. This reservoir is used to store water for our town. 这个水库是用来为我们小镇储存水的。', '形容词: storable 名词: storer 过去式: stored 过去分词: stored 现在分词: storing 第三人称单数: stores');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('curiosity', '[ˌkjʊri\'ɑːsəti]', 'n.好奇心；好奇；稀奇的人或物', '1. The child showed a healthy curiosity. 那孩子有好奇心，这是好现象。 2. Her curiosity was piqued. 她产生了好奇心。 3. I had to explain the reasons to satisfy his curiosity. 我只好解释原因来满足他的好奇心。 4. The rumors excite her curiosity. 谣言引起了她的好奇心。', '名词复数: curiosities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('detail', '[\'diːteɪl]', 'n.细节；琐事；枝节 vt.详述；详细说明', '1. The full details of the agreement haven\'t been made public. 协议的细节尚未公布。 2. He told us the accident in detail. 他详细地把事故讲给我们听。 3. He explained it so clearly that I could understand every detail. 他把它解释得很清楚,每一个细节我都明白了。 4. Sadat seemed free of the obsession with detail. 萨达特不那么注重细微末节。 5. Could you detail all your expenses on this form? 请把你的各项开支列在这张表格上，好吗？', '名词: detailer 过去式: detailed 过去分词: detailed 现在分词: detailing 第三人称单数: details');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fellowship', '[\'feloʊʃɪp]', 'n.友谊；团体；会员资格；奖学金', '1. They offer students counselling and fellowship. 他们向学生提供辅导并伸出友谊之手。 2. They offered him the hand of fellowship when he was in difficulties. 当他身处困境时，他们向他伸出了友谊之手。 3. Aleck belonged to a fellowship of revenge. 亚力克属于一个报仇团体。 4. After their initial expedition to Dujiangyan, members of Mr Sun\'s fellowship were soon faced with a number of organisational and logistical constraints. 在抵达都江堰后不久，成都天主教青年团体的成员就遇到了许多组织与后勤方面的约束。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('network', '[\'netwɜːrk]', 'n.网点；网络；网状系统；广播公司', '1. The fabrics are merchandised through a network of dealers. 通过经销网点销售纺织品。 2. The Internet is a worldwide computer network. 因特网是一个全球计算机网络系统。 3. She gave me a diagram of railway network. 她给了我一张铁路网图解。 4. The broadcast was carried on national network . 这个节目通过全国广播网进行广播。', '名词: networker 过去式: networked 过去分词: networked 现在分词: networking 第三人称单数: networks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('harbor', '[\'hɑːbə]', 'n.海港；避难所 vt.庇护；心怀；窝藏 vi.生存；进入避祸所', '1. The ship steamed into the harbor. 船驶入了港湾。 2. The bombers made a sudden strike on the harbor. 轰炸机对这港口进行了一次突然袭击。 3. They also harbor exotic life-forms, far below the reach of sunlight. 他们也是外来的生物避难所，远远低于阳光的到达。 4. They harbored refugees in times of war. 他们在战争期间收留难民。 5. The Earth is the only world known so far to harbor life. 据我们所知,地球是唯一维持生物生存的世界。', '名词: harborer 过去式: harbored 过去分词: harbored 现在分词: harboring 第三人称单数: harbors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mosaic', '[moʊ\'zeɪɪk]', 'n.马赛克；镶嵌图案 v.镶嵌；用马赛克装饰 adj.【大写】摩西的', '1. I stared for hours at the elaborate pattern in the mosaic. 我对着马赛克上精密的图案注视了好几个小时。 2. Archaeologists have worked for years to piece together the huge mosaic. 考古学家经年累月拼组这幅巨大的马赛克。 3. It\'s a rich mosaic of meadows, rivers and woods. 这是一幅由草地，河流，树木组成的五光十色的镶嵌画。 4. The sky this morning was a mosaic of blue and white. 今天早上的天空是幅蓝白相间的画面。 5. Mosaic a design on a rosewood box. 将一个图案嵌入红木盒子上。', '名词: mosaicist 过去式: mosaicked 过去分词: mosaicked 现在分词: mosaicking 第三人称单数: mosaics');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tin', '[tɪn]', 'n.锡；罐头；听头 adj.锡制的 vt.镀锡于', '1. We fuse copper and tin to make bronze. 我们把铜和锡熔制成青铜。 2. They\'d mined the hillside for tin. 他们曾在小山坡上开采锡。 3. I caught her with her fingers in the biscuit tin. 我看见她手指还在饼干盒里呢。 4. The paint had solidified in the tin. 罐子里的颜料已经乾了。 5. Tin cxxx pots or iron cxxx pots are of no use to me. 锡制的咖啡壶和铁制的咖啡壶对我而言也是没用的。', '过去式: tinned 过去分词: tinned 现在分词: tinning 第三人称单数: tins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('namely', '[\'neɪmli]', 'adv.即；也就是', '1. Labor has twoness, namely specific work and abstract work. 劳动具有二重性，即具体劳动与抽象劳动。 2. Myopia can be divided kind, namely high myopia and common myopia. 近视可以分两种，即高度近视和普通近视。 3. The railroad connects two cities, namely, New York and Chicago. 铁路连接了两个城市，即纽约与芝加哥。 4. Only one student passed the exam, namely John. 只有一个学生通过了考试，也就是约翰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('orchard', '[\'ɔːrtʃərd]', 'n.果园', '1. The children were skylarking in the orchard. 孩子们在果园里嬉戏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('herb', '[ɜːrb]', 'n.药草；香草', '1. He alighted on a rare medical herb. 他偶然找到了一种稀有的草药。 2. I had to take the herb tea although it\'s bitter. 虽然汤药很苦，我还是不得不喝了。 3. The essence drawn out from this medicinal herb is good for high blood pressure. 从这种药草提炼出来的精华对治疗高血压有效。 4. This herb can act as an antidote against snakebite. 这种药草可以用作被蛇咬后的解毒药。', '形容词: herby');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('institute', '[\'ɪnstɪtuːt]', 'n.学院；学会；协会 vt.开始；制定；创立', '1. New methods of teaching foreign languages are adopted in this institute. 该学院采用新的外语教学法。 2. Integrity and professionalism are the two main corporate values of the Institute. 诚信和专业精神是学会的两个主要机构价值观。 3. The UK\'s Securities & Investment Institute provides education and qualifications for many of these staff. 英国证券与投资协会为许多这样的员工提供培训和资格证书。 4. The police instituted an inquiry into the cause of the accident. 警方开始调查事故的原因。', '名词: instituter 过去式: instituted 过去分词: instituted 现在分词: instituting 第三人称单数: institutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('orientation', '[ˌɔːriən\'teɪʃn]', 'n.适应；定位；情况介绍；信仰；倾向；[计]定向；（学生）迎新会', '1. I needed some orientation at this stage. 我在这个阶段需要熟悉情况。 2. The arrangement must show a preferred orientation. 排列还必须呈现特定的指向。 3. The following action steps are a part of the foreman\'s orientation of the new worker. 以下内容是工头指导新工人时应采取的部分措施:介绍新的工作。 4. Christian Church that truly welcomes everybody disregarding your sexual orientation or denomination. 一个不论宗派及性取向，真正欢迎所有人的基督信仰教会。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('money', '[\'mʌni]', 'n.财产；钱；货币', '1. He robs her of money. 他抢夺她的财产。 2. Time is money. 时间就是金钱。 3. Money doesn\'t always bring happiness. 金钱并不一定带来快乐。 4. She accepted the money with mingled feelings. 她悲喜交集地收下了这笔钱。', '名词复数: moneys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bowling', '[\'boʊlɪŋ]', 'n.保龄球', '1. Prinne was tired after bowling for half an hour. 普林玩了半个钟头保龄球戏后觉得累了。 2. Jerry and Marcy are bowling on bowling night. 杰瑞和玛西在保龄球之夜打保龄球。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('storm', '[stɔːrm]', 'n.暴风雨 v.起风暴；猛攻；暴怒；捣毁', '1. In the storm I took shelter under the tree. 暴风雨时，我正在树下躲避。 2. A storm arose during the night. 夜间起风暴了。 3. The clouds threatened a big storm. 乌云预示着暴风雨即将来临。 4. Help was lacking at sea during the storm. 起风暴时海上无处可求援。', '过去式: stormed 过去分词: stormed 现在分词: storming 第三人称单数: storms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scandal', '[\'skændl]', 'n.丑闻；反感；耻辱；中伤', '1. The scandal caused tempests in the newspaper. 那件丑闻在报纸上引起阵阵风波。 2. The villagers knew about the scandal. 村子里的居民知道这件丑事。 3. This scandal may topple the government. 这桩丑闻有可能使政府垮台。 4. The President is at the center of a recent scandal over revelation about his financial interests. 总统因近来被揭露涉嫌金融权益问题而成为丑闻的主角。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('irrespective', '[ˌɪrɪ\'spektɪv]', 'adj.不顾的；不考虑的', '1. The laws apply to everyone irrespective of race, color, or creed. 法律对人人都适用，不分种族，肤色或信仰。 2. We will have the work done, irrespective of cost. 不管花多大代价,我们也要把这项工作做好。 3. He rushed toward to help, irrespective of the consequence. 他不顾后果，冲上前去帮助。 4. He married her, irrespective of the will of his parents. 他违背父母的意愿与她结了婚。', '副词: irrespectively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('liquid', '[\'lɪkwɪd]', 'adj.液体的；液态的；清澈的；清脆的；已转化成现款的（财） n.液体', '1. The doctor recommended that the patient be fed liquid food. 医生建议病人应吃流质食物。 2. Air whether in the gaseous or liquid state is a fluid. 空气，无论是气态的还是液态的，都是一种流体。 3. The earth is believed to have a liquid core. 人们相信地球有一个液态核。 4. Kate is a pretty girl with large liquid eyes. 凯特是一个有一双水汪汪大眼睛的漂亮姑娘。 5. Plasma is clear yellow liquid. 血浆是种透明淡黄的液体。', '副词: liquidly 名词: liquidness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surrender', '[sə\'rendər]', 'v.投降；屈服；放弃 n.投降；屈服；放弃', '1. It was shameful of them to surrender. 他们投降是可耻的。 2. We would rather die than surrender. 我们宁死而不投降。 3. They surrendered to the enemy. 他们向敌人投降了。 4. We can never surrender to him. 而我们绝对不能够屈服。 5. The garrison was starved into surrender. 卫戍部队因遭到断粮而投降。', '过去式: surrendered 过去分词: surrendered 现在分词: surrendering 第三人称单数: surrenders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stroll', '[stroʊl]', 'n.闲逛；漫步 v.闲逛；漫步', '1. She decided to take a stroll in the garden. 她决定在花园散步。 2. A stroll round the garden hardly qualifies as exercise! 在花园转转算不上锻炼！ 3. My father sometimes goes out for a stroll with a stick in his hand. 父亲有时候带着手杖出去散步。 4. A casual stroll through a lunatic asylum shows that faith does not prove anything. 疯人院的一次闲庭漫步说明信念并不能证明一切。 5. We stroll through a meadow full of tall grass. 我们漫步走过长满高草的牧场。', '过去式: strolled 过去分词: strolled 现在分词: strolling 第三人称单数: strolls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pure', '[pjʊr]', 'adj.纯的；纯洁的；纯粹的', '1. Water can be made pure by distilling it. 水可以通过蒸馏而提纯。 2. They are all made of one-hundred percent pure silk. 它们都是用100%的纯丝绸做成的。 3. Life is a sweet thing for one who has a pure conscience. 对于善良纯洁的人来说,生活是一件美好的事情。 4. The look from her eye is still so pure, like a dustless crystal. 她的眼神依旧清纯,仿佛水晶般纤尘不染。', '副词: purely 比较级: purer 最高级: purest 名词: pureness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enquire', '[ɪn\'kwaɪər]', 'v.询问；调查', '1. She wrote to enquire the cause of the delay. 她只得写信去询问拖延的理由。 2. I called the station to enquire about train times. 我打电话到车站询问火车时刻。 3. I\'m writing to enquire about language courses. 特此致函询问有关语言课程事宜。 4. I must enquire further into this matter. 我要进一步调查此事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preliminary', '[prɪ\'lɪmɪneri]', 'adj.初步的；预备的；开始的 n.初步行动；准备；初步措施', '1. They have made a preliminary investigation. 他们已经做了初步的调查。 2. Our team got beaten in the preliminary rounds of the competition. 我们队在这次比赛的预赛中遭淘汰。 3. Movies at the preliminary stage were silent. 电影在初期是无声的。 4. There are a lot of preliminaries to be gone through before you can visit a foreign country. 在出访外国之前要做好许多准备工作。', '副词: preliminarily 名词复数: preliminaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('translation', '[træns\'leɪʃn]', 'n.翻译；译文；RNA的转录；平移', '1. I am making a verbal translation. 我正在逐字的翻译。 2. The effect of the novel loses in translation. 这部小说经过翻译失色不少。 3. I think her translation of the article is much better than his. 我认为她对这篇文章的翻译要比他强的多。 4. Invariance under translation in time leads to conservation of energy. 在时间平移下的不变性导致能量守恒。', '形容词: translational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fashion', '[\'fæʃn]', 'n.时尚；风格；样子 vt.形成；塑造', '1. She was the queen of fashion during the 60s. 她是60年代的时尚女王。 2. Research shows that men are beginning to follow fashion. 研究显示,男性也开始像女性那样追求时尚。 3. She paints in the fashion of Picasso. 她模仿毕加索的绘画风格。 4. He only put a bit on his plate to make fashion. 他只是拨了一点食物到盘子里做做样子。 5. He managed to fashion a doll from a piece of wood. 他成功地用木块制成了一个玩具娃娃。', '名词: fashioner 过去式: fashioned 过去分词: fashioned 现在分词: fashioning 第三人称单数: fashions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shampoo', '[ʃæm\'puː]', 'n.洗发剂；洗涤剂；洗头 vt.洗（头发；地毯等）', '1. She wetted her hair and then put shampoo on it. 她把头发弄湿后抹上洗发剂。 2. I rinsed the shampoo out of my hair. 我把头发上的洗发剂冲洗乾净了。 3. He sponged down the car to remove the shampoo. 他用海绵把汽车上的洗涤剂擦掉了。 4. I want a haircut, and a shampoo. 我要理发并洗头。', '名词: shampooer 名词复数: shampoos 过去式: shampooed 过去分词: shampooed 现在分词: shampooing 第三人称单数: shampoos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('health', '[helθ]', 'n.健康；医疗保健', '1. Smoking is harmful to your health. 吸烟对你的健康有害。 2. Fresh air and exercise are good for the health. 新鲜空气和运动有益于健康。 3. It is generally believed that health is above wealth. 一般人都相信健康重于财富。 4. Hospital mamagers are urging the government to spend more on health. 医院的管理者们要求政府在医疗保健上加大支出。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('retain', '[rɪ\'teɪn]', 'vt.保持；保留；记住；聘请', '1. His speech could not retain the interest of his audience. 他的讲话不能保持住听众的兴趣。 2. I will retain my right. 我将保留我的权力。 3. Does it retain the key elements of the original story? 它是否保留了原作的关键要素? 4. She has a good memory and finds it easy to retain matters. 她记忆力好,很容易记住事情。', '形容词: retainable 名词: retainability 过去式: retained 过去分词: retained 现在分词: retaining 第三人称单数: retains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dinner', '[\'dɪnər]', 'n.晚餐；晚宴；主餐', '1. It\'s time for dinner. 该吃晚饭了。 2. It is now his turn to set me up to a nice dinner. 现在轮到他请我吃一顿丰盛的晚餐了。 3. We invite her to have Thanksgiving dinner with us. 我们邀请她和我们一起吃感恩节晚餐。 4. Because my husband has gone to a stag dinner, I have to stay at home alone. 因为我丈夫去参加一个只许男人参加的宴会，我只好独自待在家里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beloved', '[bɪ\'lʌvd]', 'adj.心爱的 n.爱人', '1. Her beloved broach was nowhere to be found. 她心爱的饰针找不到了。 2. She refused to be parted from her beloved cat. 她拒绝和她心爱的猫分开。 3. She is bewailing the loss of her beloved husband. 她在为失去心爱的丈夫而痛哭。 4. He is beloved by all. 他是众人所爱戴的。 5. Wherefore are you, my beloved? 你怎么啦，我的宝贝？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beware', '[bɪ\'wer]', 'v.小心；谨防', '1. Beware what you do with this dangerous substance. 摆弄这东西要小心。 2. Beware, it could hurt if thrown with great vigor! 但抛撒大米可得小心，用劲大了，会伤着人的。 3. Beware beloved of doctors and healers. 谨防医生和疗愈者，亲爱的。 4. I was told to beware pickpockets. 人们告诉我要谨防扒手。', '过去式: bewared 过去分词: bewared 现在分词: bewaring 第三人称单数: bewares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trait', '[treɪt]', 'n.特征；特点；少许；一笔', '1. They suddenly exhibit a striking new trait. 它们突然呈现出一种新的显著特征。 2. One of his less attractive traits is criticizing his wife in public. 他有个不大讨人喜欢的特点，就是爱当众责备妻子。 3. Our CEO talks and behaves without a trait of authority. 我们公司的首席执行官言行举止没有一点官气。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('still', '[stɪl]', 'adj.静止的；不动的；静寂的 adv.更；仍然；静止地 v.使...平静下来 n.蒸馏器；寂静；定格照', '1. Beware of silent dog and still water. 提防不吠的犬,小心静止的水。 2. The room was still at the end of the speech. 演讲结束的时候，房间里寂静无声。 3. Although she felt ill, she still went to work. 她虽然觉得身体不舒服，但仍然去上班了。 4. Although he is eighty,he is still very much alive. 他虽有八十岁了,但仍然充满了活力。 5. The food stilled the baby\'s cries. 食物使婴儿停止了哭泣。', '比较级: stiller 最高级: stillest 过去式: stilled 过去分词: stilled 现在分词: stilling 第三人称单数: stills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tolerate', '[\'tɑːləreɪt]', 'vt.容许；忍受；容忍', '1. The school cannot tolerate cheating on exams. 该学校不容许在考试中有作弊现象。 2. We do not tolerate any form of discrimination. 我们绝不容许歧视的存在。 3. He can not tolerate the extremes of heat in the desert. 他忍受不住沙漠里的酷热。 4. I cannot tolerate your rudeness. 我无法忍受你的粗鲁。', '形容词: tolerative 名词: tolerator 过去式: tolerated 过去分词: tolerated 现在分词: tolerating 第三人称单数: tolerates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fun', '[fʌn]', 'n.乐趣；玩笑 adj.有趣的', '1. I\'m learning to cook, just for the fun of it. 我正在学做饭，做著玩儿而已。 2. You\'ll sure to have fun at the party tonight. 你在今晚的晚会上一定会玩得很开心。 3. People make fun of her because she always speaks foolishly. 人们嘲笑她，因为她常说傻话。 4. Laugh is an expression of happiness, joy, silliness or fun. 笑是用来表达幸福,喜悦,可笑或玩笑等的表情! 5. Swimming in the sea is great fun. 在海里游泳很好玩。', '过去式: funned 过去分词: funned 现在分词: funning 第三人称单数: funs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mercy', '[\'mɜːrsi]', 'n.仁慈；怜悯；恩惠；宽恕', '1. Mercy to the enemies means cruelty to the people. 对敌人的仁慈就意味着对人民的残忍。 2. They showed their enemies no mercy. 他们不给敌人半点仁慈。 3. They never appealed to us for mercy. 他们从不向我们乞求怜悯。 4. The commander showed mercy to the prisoners of war. 司令官对战俘十分怜悯。', '名词复数: mercies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('allege', '[ə\'ledʒ]', 'vt.断言；宣称', '1. The newspapers allege that the police shot the suspect without warning. 报纸指称说警察未经示警就枪杀那位嫌疑犯。 2. So they alleged, but have they any proof? 他们是这样宣称的，但他们有证据吗？ 3. The police alleged that the man was murdered but they have given no proof. 警方声称这男子是被谋杀的，但未提出任何证据。 4. In your statement you allege that the accused man was seen at the scene of the crime . 在你的口供中，你供述曾经看到被告在犯罪现场。', '形容词: allegeable 名词: alleger 过去式: alleged 过去分词: alleged 现在分词: alleging 第三人称单数: alleges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('browse', '[braʊz]', 'v.浏览；随意观看；吃草 n.嫩叶；浏览', '1. He likes to browse through the books in the public library. 他喜欢在公立图书馆浏览各种书籍。 2. I spent hours browsing in the bookstore. 我花了几个小时在书店里浏览图书。 3. You are welcome to come in and browse. 欢迎您光临本店随便看看。 4. The deer mainly browse on wild vegetation not crops. 鹿主要吃野生植物，而不是吃庄稼。 5. I had a browse through the books on the shelf. 我浏览了一遍书架上的书。', '过去式: browsed 过去分词: browsed 现在分词: browsing 第三人称单数: browses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fling', '[flɪŋ]', 'vt.投；粗暴地推向 ...；猛冲；激动地说；全身心投入 n.投掷；一时的行乐；漫不经心的一段(尝试或感情) vi.急冲；(动物)猛跳', '1. Boys like to fling stones into water. 男孩子们喜欢向水中投石子。 2. She flung the papers on the desk and leave angrily. 决策层 3. She flung herself in front of a car. 她猛然冲到汽车前面。 4. You must be certain of your facts before you start flinging accusations (around) (at people). 必须对实情胸有成竹才能理直气壮地(到处)指责(别人)。 5. He had his fling before he was drafted. 他在应征入伍之前尽情行乐了一番。 6. She flung on her coat and ran to the bus-stop. 她匆匆穿上大衣就向公共汽车站跑去。', '过去式: flung 过去分词: flung 现在分词: flinging 第三人称单数: flings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('boycott', '[\'bɔɪkɑːt]', 'vt.抵制（贸易）；拒绝参加', '1. He urged all citizens to boycott Korean goods. 他呼吁所有民众联手抵制韩国货。 2. We boycott all products tested on animals. 我们抵制用动物做产品实验。 3. We boycott some country because it hurts our ego. 我们抵制某国货，因为他伤了我们的面子。 4. We are determined to boycott them. 我们决定拒绝跟他们来往。', '名词: boycotter 过去式: boycotted 过去分词: boycotted 现在分词: boycotting 第三人称单数: boycotts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reference', '[\'refrəns]', 'n.参考；参照；出处；推荐人；推荐函 v.注明出处；附参考资料', '1. This book is for reference only. 这本书仅供参考。 2. This frame of reference will be determined by the limitations on the rational man\'s knowledge. 这个参照系统决定于理性人知识的限制。 3. Full reference citations are available on the readings page. 全部参考资料的出处可以在阅读资料那页找到。 4. Can we contact your references? 我可以与你的推荐人联系吗? 5. Paraphrasing is not direct quotation, but you still need to reference it. 意译不是直接引用', '形容词: referential 副词: referentially 名词: referencer 过去式: referenced 过去分词: referenced 现在分词: referencing 第三人称单数: references');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('formation', '[fɔːr\'meɪʃn]', 'n.形成；队形；编队；构造；[地]地层', '1. Let us now examine the process of its formation. 我们现在就来研究这个形成过程。 2. School life has a great influence on the formation of a child\'s character. 学校生活对小孩个性的形成有很大影响。 3. The airplanes few over in formation. 飞机编成队形在空中飞过。 4. The troops lined up in parade formation. 部队排成阅兵队形。', '形容词: formational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('headache', '[\'hedeɪk]', 'n.头痛', '1. I\'ve got a headache. 我头痛。 2. The aspirins eased my headache. 阿司匹林使我头疼减轻。 3. I\'ve got a splitting headache. 我头疼得要裂开似的。 4. This is another big headache for him. 这是另一件使他非常头痛的事。', '形容词: headachy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mission', '[\'mɪʃn]', 'n.使命；代表团；任务；布道', '1. The minister was sent to Spain on mission. 这位部长奉命前往西班牙。 2. My mission in life is to help poor people. 我的天职是帮助穷人。 3. A Chinese trade mission has been dispatched to Japan. 一个中国贸易代表团已被派往日本。 4. Her mission was to reclaim former criminals. 她的任务是感化过去的罪犯。', '形容词: missional 过去式: missioned 过去分词: missioned 现在分词: missioning 第三人称单数: missions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stair', '[ster]', 'n.楼梯', '1. The child was sitting on the bottom stair. 那孩子正坐在楼梯最下面的一级上。 2. Clutch stair armrest, move carefully step by step. 抓紧楼梯扶手，一步步谨慎地移动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('my', '[maɪ]', 'adj.我的（I的所有格形式） int.哎呦（用于表示惊讶的感叹词）', '1. My phone was out of order. 我的电话坏了。 2. You mistook my meaning entirely. 你完全误解了我的意思。 3. My friend invited me to dine out. 我的朋友邀请我出去吃饭。 4. My! Just look at all those beautiful cakes! 哎呦！过来看看那些所有的好看的蛋糕！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blue', '[bluː]', 'adj.蓝色的；忧郁的；沮丧的；色情的 n.蓝色', '1. She wore a dark blue coat. 她穿着一件深蓝色的上衣。 2. The pots are made with blue enamel. 这些锅上有蓝色的搪瓷。 3. Someone has flown off with my blue bag. 有人把我那蓝色的包偷拿走了。 4. I\'m feeling blue today. 我今天的心情不好。 5. The color scheme of the room is blue and gold. 这个房间的色彩配置是蓝色和金黄色。', '副词: bluely 比较级: bluer 最高级: bluest 名词: blueness 过去式: blued 过去分词: blued 现在分词: bluing 第三人称单数: blues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suite', '[swiːt]', 'n.套房；一套物件；随员；[计]一组程序；[音]组曲', '1. The suite is for the honeymoon couple. 这套房是为新婚夫妇设的。 2. He brought a three-piece suite for his new house. 他为新房子买了三件一套的家具。 3. He left the hotel with his suites yesterday. 他昨天带着一群随员离开了那家酒店。 4. He has composed a suite of music for the film. 他为该电影配写了一套乐曲。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('triangle', '[\'traɪæŋɡl]', 'n.三角(形)', '1. He outlined the triangle in red. 他用红笔画出三角形。 2. The angles of a triangle total 180. 三角形的三角之和等于180°。 3. The place is a cobbled triangle. 这个地方是一块铺石子的三角地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reserve', '[rɪ\'zɜːrv]', 'vt.保留；预订；延期 n.候补；预备品；贮存 n.含蓄；克制', '1. We reserve the right to lodge a claim for loss. 我们保留要求赔偿损失的权利。 2. I have reserved a table at the restaurant. 我已在饭店预订了一桌菜。 3. The court will reserve judgement. 法庭将延期判决。 4. He has played very well on the reserve side but this chance in the first team should put him on his mettle. 他在候补队中表现非常出色,但这次作为正式队员参赛将对他的能力进行考验。 5. He spoke with reserve. 他说话谨慎。', '形容词: reservable 名词: reserver 过去式: reserved 过去分词: reserved 现在分词: reserving 第三人称单数: reserves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rid', '[rɪd]', 'vt.摆脱；除去', '1. We will be glad to get rid of him. 摆脱他，我们将很高兴。 2. You must rid yourself of this melancholy mood. 你一定要摆脱这种忧愁情绪。 3. We must try every way to rid ourselves of these debts. 我们要想尽一切办法来摆脱这些债务。 4. It is necessary to get rid of bureaucratic practices. 必须清除官僚习气。', '名词: ridder 过去式: rid/ridded 过去分词: rid/ridded 现在分词: ridding 第三人称单数: rids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bathroom', '[\'bæθruːm]', 'n.浴室；<美>洗手间', '1. He weighed himself on the bathroom scales. 他在浴室的磅秤上称体重。 2. Steam has fogged the bathroom mirror. 水蒸气把浴室里的镜子遮住了。 3. There are two bathrooms in my house. 我们家有两个浴室。 4. Every room in the hotel has a private bathroom. 旅馆中的每个房间都有一个单独浴室。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spoil', '[spɔɪl]', 'v.宠坏；溺爱；破坏；腐坏；使索然无味 n.战利品；奖品', '1. A fond mother may spoil her child. 溺爱的母亲可能会宠坏她的孩子。 2. The child was spoilt by his grandfather. 这个孩子被他的爷爷给惯坏了。 3. The children kept quarreling and spoiled our holiday. 孩子们不断吵架，破坏了我们的假期。 4. He had spoiled the soup by putting in too much salt. 他往汤里放盐太多，把汤给糟蹋了。 5. The invaders made spoil of all in their way. 侵略者所到之处无不洗劫一空。', '过去式: spoiled/spoilt 过去分词: spoiled/spoilt 现在分词: spoiling 第三人称单数: spoils');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sue', '[suː]', 'vt.控告；起诉 vi.请求；起诉', '1. If you don\'t complete the work, I will sue you for damages. 如果你不把工作做完,我就要控告你支付赔偿。 2. Lucy is going to sue Antony for breach of promise. 露西准备控告安东尼毁婚约。 3. They feel very angry because Cathy is going to sue Tony. 他们感到非常的生气,因为凯西即将要起诉托尼。 4. She decided to sue her employer for wrongful dismissal. 她决定起诉雇主非法解雇她。 5. You can sue to the committee for permission. 你可以向委员会请求获准。', '名词: suer 过去式: sued 过去分词: sued 现在分词: suing 第三人称单数: sues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sufficient', '[sə\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.足够的；充分的', '1. The money I have saved is sufficient for buying a car. 我所存的钱足以买一辆汽车。 2. I doubt whether they really have sufficient manpower. 我怀疑他们是否真有足够的人力。 3. There is sufficient food for everybody. 有足够的饭菜供大家吃。 4. We must work hard, but equally we must get sufficient rest. 我们必须努力工作,但同时也要有充分的休息。', '副词: sufficiently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slim', '[slɪm]', 'adj.苗条的；微小的；细长的 v.减肥；缩减', '1. I wish I was as slim as you. 但愿我能像你一样苗条 2. I remember her (ie picture her in my mind) as a slim young girl. 我想起她那时还是个苗条的少女。 3. He showed much enthusiasm for our plan.1329286376:435972 滚开 4. I have a slim gold watch. 我有一块细长的金表。 5. She is trying to slim by jogging. 她正用跑步法来减肥。', '副词: slimly 比较级: slimmer 最高级: slimmest 名词: slimmer 过去式: slimmed 过去分词: slimmed 现在分词: slimming 第三人称单数: slims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('differ', '[\'dɪfər]', 'vi.不同；有区别', '1. They differ widely in their opinions. 他们的意见分歧很大。 2. Our ideologies differ. 我们的思想不同。 3. They differ in size but not in kind. 这些东西的区别只是大小不同而实质一样。 4. Although our looks differ, we are both attractive. 尽管我俩相貌不同，但都讨人喜欢。', '过去式: differed 过去分词: differed 现在分词: differing 第三人称单数: differs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('persevere', '[ˌpɜːrsə\'vɪr]', 'v.坚持；不屈不挠', '1. When things get difficult, you just have to grit your teeth and persevere. 遇到困难只需咬紧牙关坚持下去。 2. If you persevere with work, you\'ll succeed in the end. 你如果把工作坚持下去，最终会取得成功的。 3. He was hopeless at French, but his teacher persevered with him. 他怎么也学不会法语,可是老师仍锲而不舍地帮助他。', '副词: perseveringly 过去式: persevered 过去分词: persevered 现在分词: persevering 第三人称单数: perseveres');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('agenda', '[ə\'dʒendə]', 'n.议事日程', '1. This agenda will form the basis of our next meeting. 本议程将成为下次会议的中心议题。 2. Let\'s go on to the next item on the agenda. 我们讨论议程表上的下一项吧。 3. Let\'s thrash the matter over before putting it on the agenda. 我们先把这件事仔细研究一下，再把它列入议事日程。', '名词复数: agendas');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interior', '[ɪn\'tɪriər]', 'adj.内地的；国内的；内部的 n.内部；内在', '1. The people of the African interior began to offer gold in exchange for the goods they needed from abroad. 从此后非洲内地的各族人民开始用黄金交换他们所需要的外国货物。 2. Despite this, at the Siberian station stops, the still heat of the Russian interior burned the skin within seconds and the silence echoed. 尽管如此，在西伯利亚车站停车的时候，瞬间就能感受到俄罗斯内地的炎热烧灼皮肤，沉寂的大地也有了回声。 3. They are engaged in interior trade. 他们从事国内贸易。 4. We are fascinated by the delicate interior design of the apartment. 我们被这所公寓的精致的室内装潢设计吸引。 5. Xi\'an is a city in the interior of China. 西安是一个内陆城市。', '副词: interiorly 名词: interiority');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adhere', '[əd\'hɪr]', 'vi.遵守；坚持；粘附', '1. They failed to adhere to our original agreement. 他们未能遵守我们原定的协议。 2. We should adhere to our opinions. 我们应当坚持我们的意见。 3. We adhere to the principle stand of marxism. 我们坚持马克思主义思想原则。 4. The new paint won\'t adhere to the walls so I\'ll have to strip it all off and start from scratch. 新涂的油漆粘不住墙壁,因此我得把它全部刮掉,重新刷过。', '过去式: adhered 过去分词: adhered 现在分词: adhering 第三人称单数: adheres');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('god', '[ɡɑːd]', 'n.神；偶像；(复数)<英>剧院顶层楼座的观众；(大写)上帝 int.天呐', '1. Poseidon was the Greek god of the sea. 波赛冬是希腊海神。 2. The Greeks dedicated a shrine to the god. 希腊人把一座庙奉献给神。 3. He\'s one of the gods of the fashion world. 他是时尚界的偶像之一。 4. God bless you! 愿上帝保佑你！ 5. Oh, my god! I cleared all my data. 啊，我的天！我把所有资料都消掉了！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deficit', '[\'defɪsɪt]', 'n.赤字；逆差；亏损；亏空；不足', '1. The current trade deficit indicates a serious imbalance between our import and export trade. 当前的贸易赤字表明我们的进出口贸易严重失调。 2. That would still leave a substantial trade deficit. 这样仍然会出现巨额贸易逆差。 3. We have a great deficit this year. 我们今年有很大亏损。 4. The company had a deficit of 5000 dollars. 公司亏空了五千美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('both', '[boʊθ]', 'adj.两者的 pron.两者 conj.不但 ... 而且 ...', '1. Both his eyes are hurt. 他的两眼都受伤了。 2. She kissed him on both cheeks. 她吻了他的双颊。 3. Both are good. 两者都好。 4. Both of us knew it. 我们两个都知道这件事。 5. He is both a soldier and a poet. 他既是个战士，又是个诗人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('debate', '[dɪ\'beɪt]', 'n.辩论；讨论 vt.争论；思考 vi.辩论', '1. After a long debate, the house of commons approved the bill. 经过长时间的辩论，下议院通过了议案。 2. We had a long debate as to whether we should spend so much money on space technology. 至于我们要否花那么多钱在太空技术上,我们辩论了很久。 3. Her resignation caused much public debate. 她辞职一事引起群众议论纷纷。 4. There has been heated debate about whether the film should be allowed. 关于这场电影是否该通过,人们展开了热烈的讨论。 5. I don\'t wish to debate my opinions with you. 我不想就我的看法同你辩论。 6. This is a question that they have often debated. 这是个他们常讨论的问题。', '名词: debatement 过去式: debated 过去分词: debated 现在分词: debating 第三人称单数: debates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plus', '[plʌs]', 'prep.加；加上 adj.正的；超过的 n.正数；加号；优势 conj.并且', '1. Two plus five is seven. 二加五等于七。 2. The bill was 10, plus 1 for postage. 帐款是10英镑，再加上1英镑邮费。 3. We\'ve got to fit five people plus all their luggage in the car. 我们得在汽车里挤下五个人和全部行李。 4. 5 is a plus quantity. 五是一个正数。 5. He seems to have mistaken a plus for a minus. 他似乎把正号误作负号了。 6. Their strength plus their spirit makes them formidable. Intelligence plus wit makes for an interesting person. 他们的力量再加上勇气使得他们难于战胜。智慧加上机智就会造就一个有趣的人', '名词复数: pluses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grave', '[ɡreiv]', 'n.坟墓；死亡 adj.严肃的；严重的；庄重的 v.雕刻；铭记；', '1. She laid the bouquet on the newly turfed grave. 她把那束花放置在新铺上草皮的坟墓上。 2. You are just digging your own grave if you go on smoking so heavily. 你继续这样过度吸烟，就是在自掘坟墓。 3. His face was grave when I told him my decision. 当我告诉他我的决定时，他的脸色很严肃。 4. The situation poses a grave threat to world peace. 这局势对世界和平构成了严重的威胁。', '副词: gravely 比较级: graver 最高级: gravest 名词: graveness 过去式: graved 过去分词: graven/graved 现在分词: graving 第三人称单数: graves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('file', '[faɪl]', 'n.档案；卷宗；文件；锉刀，指甲锉 vt.把 ... 归档；提出(申请书、议案等)', '1. Put this letter in the main file. 把这封信放在主要文件夹中。 2. Would you please take a seat while I look into our file? 你先坐一下,我给你查一下我们的卷宗? 3. Put this letter in the main file. 把这封信放在主要文件夹中。 4. Please file those letters. 请把这些信件存档。', '过去式: filed 过去分词: filed 现在分词: filing 第三人称单数: files');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inject', '[ɪn\'dʒekt]', 'v.注射；注入；引入；插入', '1. The nurse injected penicillin into her arm. 护士给她的胳膊注射了青霉素。 2. His medicine is a drug that can be injected or taken by mouth. 他的药可以注射或口服。 3. His appointment may inject some new life into the committee. 他的任命可能给这委员会注入新生命。 4. He injected new ideas into the discussion. 他把新的概念引入讨论中。', '名词: injector 过去式: injected 过去分词: injected 现在分词: injecting 第三人称单数: injects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ignorance', '[\'ɪɡnərəns]', 'n.无知；愚昧', '1. He tried to veil his contempt at my ignorance. 他试图掩饰对我的无知的蔑视。 2. I guess ignorance must be a sin. 我认为无知是一种罪。 3. I regret my ignorance on the subject. 我对自己对这个课题的无知感到遗憾。 4. Knowledge makes humble; ignorance makes proud. [谚]知识使人谦虚，无知使人骄傲。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plunge', '[plʌndʒ]', 'v.使投入；跳入；栽进；下降，急降，突降 n.投入；跳入', '1. She was about to plunge into something. 她就要采取什么行动了。 2. Don\'t plunge head first into another person\'s room. 别冒冒失失地撞进别人的房间。 3. The sudden jolt plunged her forward. 突然颠了一下，她向前打了个趔趄。 4. I waved my dog to plunge into the water. 我挥手示意我的狗跳入水中。 5. So why not take the plunge and have it over? 你为什么不鼓起勇气把这事赶紧解决了呢?', '过去式: plunged 过去分词: plunged 现在分词: plunging 第三人称单数: plunges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thirteen', '[ˌθɜːr\'tiːn]', 'num.十三', '1. The number thirteen is often considered unlucky. 十三这个数字常常认为是个不吉利的数字。 2. When she was thirteen, her family moved to England. 十三岁时，她们家搬到了英国。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acquisition', '[ˌækwɪ\'zɪʃn]', 'n.获得；所获之物；采集', '1. Life is a process about the acquisition of knowledge, wealth and happiness. 生命就是一个获得知识、财富和幸福的过程。 2. My classmates were attracted by the library\'s most recent acquisitions. 同学们都被图书馆最近新添的书籍吸引了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('posture', '[\'pɑːstʃər]', 'n.姿势；态度；情形 v.作 ... 姿势；摆架子', '1. Only humans have a natural upright posture. 只有人类才有自然直立的姿势。 2. The artist asked his model to take a reclining posture. 画家要求模特取斜倚着的姿势。 3. She has very good posture. 她举止很优雅。 4. The government adopted an uncompromising posture on the issue of independence. 政府在独立的问题上采取了毫不妥协的态度。 5. The war-monger would sometimes posture for peace 战争贩子有时也会装出主张和平的姿态。', '形容词: postural 名词: posturer 过去式: postured 过去分词: postured 现在分词: posturing 第三人称单数: postures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('staple', '[\'steɪpl]', 'n.U形(订书)钉；主要产物(要素)；原料(地) adj.主要的；重要的 vt.用订书机装订', '1. He used a pair of scissors to take the staple out of the document. 他用剪刀将订书钉从文件上取了出来。 2. Coffee is the staple of this district. 咖啡是这个地区的主要产品。 3. Bread, potato and other staple continue to rise in price. 面包、土豆及其他主食的价格继续上涨。 4. For example, rice is a staple crop in much of Asia. 例如，在亚洲大米是原料农作物。 5. Short stories are her staple reading. 短篇小说是她经常看的读物。 6. He stapled the paper together. 他把文件钉在一起。', '过去式: stapled 过去分词: stapled 现在分词: stapling 第三人称单数: staples');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pub', '[pʌb]', 'n.酒吧；酒馆', '1. I ran into an old friend in a pub. 我在酒吧碰到了一位老朋友。 2. We make our ritual visit to the pub. 我们照例去了酒吧。 3. I passed the pub on my way to the library. 我在去图书馆的路上经过了那个酒馆。 4. There is a dreadful shindy in the pub last night. 昨天晚上酒馆里有人大打出手。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eyesight', '[\'aɪsaɪt]', 'n.视力', '1. Is your eyesight failing recently? 你近来视力有所变差吗？ 2. The eye drops will help to improve your eyesight. 这种眼药水能改善你的视力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('welcome', '[\'welkəm]', 'vt.欢迎 adj.受欢迎的 n.欢迎 int.欢迎(客人来访或新成员的加入)', '1. I don\'t welcome intrusions into my privacy. 我不希望有人干扰我的私生活。 2. When I came into the office, the principal rose to welcome me. 当我走进办公室时,校长起身欢迎我。 3. You are always welcome to our house. 欢迎你随时到我们家。 4. Her suggestion received a rather unenthusiastic welcome. 她的建议受到冷遇。 5. Welcome to China! 欢迎到中国来！', '副词: welcomely 名词: welcomeness 过去式: welcomed 过去分词: welcomed 现在分词: welcoming 第三人称单数: welcomes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('murmur', '[\'mɜːrmər]', 'v.低语；发出连续轻柔的声音；低声抱怨 n.低语；连续轻柔的声音；低声的抱怨；[医]心区杂音', '1. Some of the sailors began to murmur about it bringing bad luck. 一些水手开始低声说这带来了噩运。 2. The old man drooped his head and began to murmur to himself my father\'s name. 老人低下头，低声念叨我父亲的名字。 3. The breeze murmured in the pines. 松林里微风沙沙作响。 4. The little stream murmured at the foot of the hill. 小溪在山脚下潺潺流动。 5. The murmur swelled into a roar. 窃窃私语的声音变大形成一片喧哗。', '形容词: murmurous 副词: murmuringly 名词: murmurer 过去式: murmured 过去分词: murmured 现在分词: murmuring 第三人称单数: murmurs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('successor', '[sək\'sesər]', 'n.接班人；继任人', '1. I am sure that he is a reliable successor. 我确信他是个可靠的接班人。 2. The chairman has designated her as his successor. 主席已指定她作为他的接班人。 3. The vice president was the president\'s successor. 副总统是总统的继任人。 4. Rumour is already rife here as to Dr. Trefoil\'s successor. 关于特雷福伊尔博士的继任人，此间已经谣言蜂起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('average', '[\'ævərɪdʒ]', 'n.平均数；平均水平 adj.平均的；一般的；通常的 v.取平均值；达到平均水平', '1. The average of 4,6 and 8 is 6. 4,6, 8的平均数是6。 2. Temperatures are below average for the time of year. 温度低于此时的年平均温度。 3. The average age of the boys in this class is fifteen. 本班男生的平均年龄是十五岁。 4. Tom\'s work at school is above the average. 汤姆的功课是中上等水平。 5. If you average 4, 6 and 11,you get 7 . 如果你将4，6和11平均，你即得7。', '副词: averagely 名词: averageness 过去式: averaged 过去分词: averaged 现在分词: averaging 第三人称单数: averages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('organize', '[\'ɔːrɡənaɪz]', 'v.组织；安排；筹办', '1. The meeting was badly organized. 会议组织得很糟。 2. They planned to organize a scientific expedition. 他们计划组织一次科学考察。 3. I was asked to organize the trip, but I messed it up. 大家要我组织这次旅游，可是我把事情搞糟了。 4. He was going to organize everything properly. 他要把一切都安排得井井有条。', '名词: organizer 过去式: organized 过去分词: organized 现在分词: organizing 第三人称单数: organizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sex', '[seks]', 'n.性别；性欲；性 vt.区别 ... 性别；引起 ... 性欲', '1. Everybody can come to this school,without respect to class, race, or sex. 不论阶级、种族、性别,人人都可以进这所学校上课。 2. She disguised her true sex under a man\'s garment. 她身穿男装来掩饰自己的真实性别。 3. Hunger and sex are elemental drives of human beings. 食欲和性欲是人类的原始冲动。 4. The movie is full of sex and violence. 这部电影充满了性和暴力。 5. It\'s difficult to sex newborn chicks. 新生小鸡雏的性别是很难判断的。', '过去式: sexed 过去分词: sexed 现在分词: sexing 第三人称单数: sexes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shake', '[ʃeɪk]', 'v.摇动；震动；握手 n.片刻；摇晃；<美口>奶昔', '1. Give the bottle a couple of shakes before pouring the juice. 倒果汁前，先把瓶子摇几下。 2. He shook his head in disapproval. 他摇了摇头表示反对。 3. His voice shook with fear. 他害怕得声音发抖。 4. It\'s time to shake out the red flag. 是把这面红旗打开的时候了。 5. He finished the bottle of wine in a shake. 他片刻功夫就把一瓶酒喝完了。', '形容词: shakable 过去式: shook 过去分词: shaken 现在分词: shaking 第三人称单数: shakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gather', '[\'ɡæðər]', 'v.聚集；集合；收集；推测 n.聚集；褶子', '1. Clouds gather before a thunderstorm. 在风暴来临之前云层聚集。 2. People began to gather outside the palace. 人们开始聚集在宫殿前。 3. We\'ll gather at the school gate at eight tomorrow. 我们明天八点在校门口集合。 4. He took the trouble to gather the materials for me. 他不辞辛劳地为我收集资料。', '名词: gatherer 过去式: gathered 过去分词: gathered 现在分词: gathering 第三人称单数: gathers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('occur', '[ə\'kɜːr]', 'vi.发生；存在；出现；想到', '1. That plane crash occurred only minutes after take-off. 空难在起飞几分钟后就发生了。 2. Misprints occur on every page. 每页都有印刷错误。 3. A connection error might occur. 可能会出现连接错误。 4. Didn\'t it occur to you that he was lying? 你当时没想到他在撒谎吗？', '过去式: occurred 过去分词: occurred 现在分词: occurring 第三人称单数: occurs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('horizontal', '[ˌhɔːrə\'zɑːntl]', 'adj.水平的；横的 n.水平线；水平面', '1. The vertical line meets the horizontal one here. 垂直线与水平线在此相交。 2. The sun rises from the horizontal line. 太阳从地平线上升起。 3. Please draw a horizontal line on the page. 请在这一页画条横线。 4. The bottom of the door is out of the horizontal. 这扇门底部不成水平。', '副词: horizontally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nonsense', '[\'nɑːnsens]', 'n.废话；胡说；荒唐', '1. You are talking complete nonsense. 你说的全是废话。 2. I have never in my entire life heard such nonsense! 我一生中从未听到过这样的废话！ 3. What he said is nonsense. 他的话纯粹是胡说。 4. We\'ll have no nonsense of that sort. 我们不能允许那种荒唐的事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quiet', '[\'kwaɪət]', 'adj.安静的；宁静的；平静的 n.安静；平静；闲适 vt.使平静；使安心 vi.平静下来', '1. When you are in a library, you must be quiet. 当你在图书馆时,你必须保持安静。 2. Please keep quiet while others are studying. 在别人学习的时候,请保持安静。 3. His health has turned all the better for him after a quiet holiday abroad. 在国外度过一个宁静的假期，他的健康状况有所好转。 4. Everything was quiet under the blinking stars. 在这闪耀的星光底下,一切都很平静。 5. Leave me alone. I just want some peace and quiet. 别理我,我只想安静一下。 6. I am well aware that nothing else will quiet Tom. 我很清楚,别的任何办法都不能使汤姆罢休。 7. When he quieted down, I began to tell him the truth. 当他平静下来时，我开始告诉他实情。', '副词: quietly 比较级: quieter 最高级: quietest 名词: quietness 过去式: quieted 过去分词: quieted 现在分词: quieting 第三人称单数: quiets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('indoor', '[\'ɪndɔːr]', 'adj.户内的；室内的', '1. People play indoor sports whatever the weather. 不论气候如何，人们都从事户内运动。 2. Billiards is a good indoor game. 台球是一种有益的户内游戏。 3. Fix the protectors on the indoor walls or windows. 将保护器固定在室内的墙壁上。 4. Buzz-Bomb Balloon is an indoor game. 流行炸弹气球是一个室内的游戏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fluid', '[\'fluːɪd]', 'n.液体；流体 adj.流动的；流畅的；不定的', '1. There\'s some sort of sticky fluid on the kitchen floor. 厨房的地上有一种发黏的液体。 2. Air is a fluid but not a liquid, while water is both a fluid and a liquid. 空气是流体不是液体，水是流体也是液体。 3. We have not enough fluid capital. 我们没有足够的流动资金。 4. The professor praised her fluid style in the composition. 教授称赞她文章中流畅的文体。', '副词: fluidly 名词: fluidity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('console', '[kən\'soʊl]', 'vt.安慰；慰藉 n.仪表盘；操控台；(游戏)平台；落地式支座', '1. I tried to console her, but in vain. 我试着去安慰她，但是无效。 2. He consoled himself with the thought that it might have been worse. 他聊以自慰的是幸亏事情没有更糟。 3. He was beyond my skill to quiet or console! 我可没有那个本事使他安静下来，或者能给他慰藉！ 4. There are many lights and electrical instruments on the computer console. 电脑控制板上有许多小灯和电子设备。', '形容词: consolable 副词: consolingly 名词: consoler 过去式: consoled 过去分词: consoled 现在分词: consoling 第三人称单数: consoles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('salvation', '[sæl\'veɪʃn]', 'n.拯救；救世；救助', '1. They hope God can give them salvation. 他们希望上帝能够拯救他们。 2. Their toils and tireless courage were our salvation. 他们艰苦的工作和不倦的勇气拯救了我们。 3. She works for the Salvation Army. 她为救世军工作。 4. After so much dry weather, the rain has been the farmer\'s salvation. 天气干旱了这么久，这场雨成了农民的救星。', '形容词: salvational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('within', '[wɪ\'ðɪn]', 'prep.在(某段时间、距离或范围)内；在…里面 adv.在…里面 n.内部', '1. I\'ll be coming within an hour. 一小时之内我就会到。 2. No fishing is allowed within a twenty mile limit. 二十英里范围内不准垂钓。 3. This is a task well within your ability. 这完全是你力所能及的工作。 4. Several cars are available within this price range. 在这个价格范围内，有好几种汽车可供选购。 5. He decorated his house within and without. 他装修房屋的里面和外面。 6. Seen from within, the cave looks larger. 从内部看这山洞显得比较大些。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('radioactive', '[\'reɪdioʊ\'æktɪv]', 'adj.放射性的', '1. Radioactive ray is material thing. 放射线是实际的物质。 2. Radium and uranium are radioactive elements. 镭和铀是放射性元素。 3. Radioactive waste must be stored on land. 有放射性的废物都必须存放在陆地上。', '副词: radioactively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disc', '[dɪsk]', 'n.唱片；圆盘；盘状物；花盘；磁盘（=disk） pref.表示“盘；盘状物；唱片” abbr.折扣（=discount）', '1. I have many discs. 我有许多唱片。 2. The compact disc is a miracle of modern technology. 激光唱片是当代技术的奇葩。 3. I bought this new Beatles disc on sale today. 今天减价时我买了这张披头士的新唱片。 4. The edge of the disc had been machined smooth. 圆盘的边缘已用机器磨光。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('superior', '[suː\'pɪriər]', 'n.上级；高手；上标 adj.高傲的；上层的；上好的；出众的', '1. He always does what his superiors tell him. 他惟上级之命是从。 2. He has no superior as a Shakespearian actor. 他演莎士比亚戏剧无出其右。 3. He smiled a superior smile as he drove past in his expensive new car. 他开着那辆豪华的新车驶过时，傲慢的微微一笑。 4. I\'ll report you to your superior officer! 我要把你的情况报告给你的上司！', '副词: superiorly 名词: superiority');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('withhold', '[wɪð\'hoʊld]', 'v.抑制；阻挡；扣留；保留', '1. The readers cannot withhold their admiration. 读者无法抑制自己的敬佩。 2. How shall I withhold from tears when we part? 我们离别时我如何忍得住眼泪呢？ 3. The dam is too weak to withhold the pressure of the rising water. 水坝不够牢固，抵挡不住水上涨的压力。 4. The board have decide to withhold part of their grant money from certain student. 委员会决定不发给某些学生的部分助学金。', '名词: withholder 过去式: withheld 过去分词: withheld 现在分词: withholding 第三人称单数: withholds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('opinion', '[ə\'pɪnjən]', 'n.意见；主张；看法；判断', '1. I can\'t agree with your opinion in this respect. 在这方面,我不赞同你的意见。 2. No matter what you say, I shall stick to my opinion. 不管你说什么,我都坚持我的主张。 3. I\'d like to have your opinion on the 1995 World Expo. 我想听听您对1995年世界博览会的看法。 4. Nixon may have been right in his judgment that there was no public opinion left to rally. 尼克松认为已经剩不下什么公众舆论好争取了，他的这个判断可能是对的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sportsman', '[\'spɔːrtsmən]', 'n.运动员', '1. We think he is an outstanding sportsman. 我们认为他是一名优秀的运动员。 2. His favourite sportsman is golfer Ian Poulter. 他最喜欢的运动员是高尔夫球员伊恩.', '形容词: sportsmanlike');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('galaxy', '[\'ɡæləksi]', 'n.银河；星系；一群杰出的人', '1. The sun is only a very small star in the Galaxy. 太阳只是银河系中一颗很小的恒星。 2. The earth is one of the planets in the Galaxy. 地球是银河系中的星球之一。 3. Each galaxy contains myriads of stars. 每一星系都有无数的恒星。 4. The solar system is a small part of our galaxy. 太阳系是我们星系的一个小部分。', '名词复数: galaxies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('year', '[jɪr]', 'n.年；年度；年龄；学年', '1. Winter is the coldest season in a year. 冬季是一年中最冷的季节。 2. The thief was put into prison for one year. 小偷被监禁一年。 3. She was designated sportswoman of the year. 她被指定为本年度的体坛明星。 4. She is sixteen years old but has a mental age of five. 她十六岁，而智力年龄是五岁。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preface', '[\'prefəs]', 'n. 序文； 绪言； 前言 v.作序，写前言；以…开始', '1. That dictionary has a preface, not a foreword. 那部词典有一篇序文，不是前言。 2. The preface contained an acknowledgment of those who had helped her. 绪言中包含她对那些帮助过她的人的致谢声明。 3. Can you sort me out on how to write this preface? 你能对怎样写这个前言给我提点建议吗？ 4. The preface of this diary recounted her life. 这本日记的前言叙述了她的生活。 5. Several pages of closely reasoned argument preface her account of the war. 她那部关于战争的著述之前有几页论证严谨的序言。', '名词: prefacer 过去式: prefaced 过去分词: prefaced 现在分词: prefacing 第三人称单数: prefaces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('package', '[\'pækɪdʒ]', 'n.包裹；整批交易 vt.把 ... 打包；把 ... 进行推销', '1. The postman brought me a large package. 邮递员给我送来一个大包裹。 2. He received a compact package. 他收到一个扎得很紧的包裹。 3. The ministers are trying to put together a package that will end the dispute. 大臣们力图搞个一揽子交易结束这场争论。 4. Before you can deploy your solution, you must package it into a CAB file. 在部署解决方案之前,你必须将其打包到CAB文件中。', '名词: packager 过去式: packaged 过去分词: packaged 现在分词: packaging 第三人称单数: packages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('underlie', '[ˌʌndər\'laɪ]', 'v.位于 ... 之下；成为 ... 的基础；[经]优先于', '1. Shale underlies coal. 页岩层在煤层之下。 2. Technology improvements underlie these trends. 科技进步将成为此发展趋势的基础。 3. Many factors underlie my decision. 我的决定以众多因素为基础 4. A deep faith underlies her work among refugees. 她在难民中工作是因为她有很深的信念。', '过去式: underlay 过去分词: underlain 现在分词: underlying 第三人称单数: underlies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('colony', '[\'kɑːləni]', 'n.殖民地；侨居地；侨民；聚居(地)；群体；菌落', '1. This country used to be a British colony in Asia. 这个国家曾是英国在亚洲的殖民地。 2. Britain was mandated to govern the former colony of German East Africa. 英国授权代管德国在东非的前殖民地。 3. That first winter in America was very hard for the new colony. 对于新侨民来说,在美国的第一个冬天是非常难熬的。 4. They live in an artists\' colony. 他们住在艺术家聚居区。', '名词复数: colonies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('perform', '[pər\'fɔːrm]', 'v.执行；履行；表演；运转；举行', '1. Every manager must perform some duties of a ceremonial nature. 每个管理者必须执行一些礼仪性的任务。 2. Student teams perform a comprehensive analysis and valuation of a business, as outlined in the syllabus. 如同课程大纲所提及，每一组学生都要对一个企业执行广泛的分析与评价。 3. They always perform their duties faithfully. 他们总是忠实地履行自己的职责。 4. We will resolutely perform our internationalist duty no matter what happens. 不管发生什么情况，我们都要坚决履行我们的国际主义义务。', '形容词: performable 名词: performer 过去式: performed 过去分词: performed 现在分词: performing 第三人称单数: performs 名词: performance');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slaughter', '[\'slɔːtər]', 'n.残杀；屠杀；大量杀戮 v.残杀；屠杀', '1. He had no strong feelings about human slaughter. 他对人类残杀没有强烈的感情。 2. I am really terrified to witness the slaughter. 我亲眼目睹这场屠杀，真是吓坏了。 3. Wholesale slaughter was carried out in the name of progress. 大规模的屠杀在维护进步的名义下进行。 4. He waded through slaughter to the throne. 他行杀戮而得王位。 5. Hundreds of innocent civilians were cruelly slaughtered. 数百名无辜平民遭残杀。', '形容词: slaughterous 名词: slaughterer 过去式: slaughtered 过去分词: slaughtered 现在分词: slaughtering 第三人称单数: slaughters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('above', '[ə\'bʌv]', 'prep.超过；在 ... 上面；高于 adj.上面的；以上的 adv.在上面；超过；更重要地；上文地 n.上面的东西', '1. The glider was soaring above the valley. 那架滑翔机在山谷上空滑翔。 2. Applicants must be above the age of 18. 申请者的年龄必须超过18岁。 3. The temperature has been above the average recently. 近来的气温一直比平均温度高。 4. The sun rose above the horizon. 太阳升到地平线上。 5. The above bedroom is mine. 上面的房间是我的。 6. We are fascinated by the stars twinkling above. 天空中闪烁的星星让我们陶醉着。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ferry', '[\'feri]', 'n.渡船；渡口 vt.摆渡；运输 vi.摆渡', '1. There\'s a good duty-free shop (ie one selling such goods) on the ferry. 渡船上有个挺不错的免税商店。 2. The sway of the ferry made him feel sick. 渡船摇摇晃晃，他感到恶心。 3. We crossed the river by ferry. 我们坐渡船过了河。 4. He went down to the ferry but found the boat on the other side. 他到了渡口，却发现渡船在对岸。 5. Two small boats ferry people back and forth. 两只小船往返为人摆渡。 6. The tourists ferried across to the opposite bank. 游客摆渡到对岸。', '名词复数: ferries 过去式: ferried 过去分词: ferried 现在分词: ferrying 第三人称单数: ferries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hat', '[hæt]', 'n.帽子 vt.给 ... 戴帽子 vi.提供帽子；制造帽子', '1. She bought a hat yesterday. 她昨天买了一顶帽子。 2. He took off the hat and revealed his bald head. 他脱下帽子，露出秃头。 3. He always wears a panama hat. 他总戴着一顶巴拿马草帽。 4. The magician conjured a rabbit out of his hat. 魔术师从他的帽子里变出一只兔子。 5. The young lady was beautifully dressed and hatted. 那位小姐身着漂亮衣服, 头戴华丽帽子。', '过去式: hatted 过去分词: hatted 现在分词: hatting 第三人称单数: hats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attitude', '[\'ætɪtuːd]', 'n.态度；看法；姿势', '1. We must maintain a firm attitude. 我们必须采取坚定的态度。 2. She shows a very positive attitude to her work. 她工作态度非常积极。 3. He has a mellow attitude to life. 他对生活有种成熟的看法。 4. As you get older, your attitude towards death changes. 人随著年龄的增长,对死亡的看法也会有所改变。', '形容词: attitudinal');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scope', '[skoʊp]', 'n.机会；范围；眼界；观看的仪器 vt.仔细研究', '1. He gets a work that gives scope for his abilities. 他得到了一份有机会发挥他才能的工作。 2. He has no scope for his particular talents. 他没有施展自己特殊才能的机会。 3. It is within my scope. 那是在我的范围之内。 4. This subject is outside the scope of our inquiry. 这个问题不在我们探讨的范围之内。 5. He scopes the big picture of Israeli-Arab relations. 他认真地查看关于以色列和阿拉伯关系的大图片。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('necessitate', '[nə\'sesɪteɪt]', 'v. 使 ... 成为必需； 迫使', '1. It would be best if these disputes could be resolved without recourse to the courts, but the broad reach of electronic networking will probably necessitate changes in common law. 如果诸如此类的争议可以不上法庭就获得解决，是最好不过了，但电子网路的无远弗届或许会迫使普通法改变。', '形容词: necessitative 名词: necessitation 过去式: necessitated 过去分词: necessitated 现在分词: necessitating 第三人称单数: necessitates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ruler', '[\'ruːlər]', 'n.尺子；划线板 n.统治者；支配者', '1. The ruler is divided into centimetres. 在尺子上分厘米刻度。 2. He reminded me not to forget to bring my ruler. 他提醒我别忘了带尺子。 3. The colonists revolted against their British ruler. 殖民地人民反抗他们的英国统治者。 4. The chairman is only the nominal ruler of the country. 主席只是那个国家名义上的统治者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('phrase', '[freɪz]', 'n.短语；习语；措辞；[音]乐句 vt.措词；将(乐曲)分成乐句', '1. The new phrase is now on the tongue of men. 这个新短语现在正十分流行。 2. The teacher dictated the phrase to the class. 老师让全班同学听写这个短语。 3. He hashed a phrase in order to colour the sentence. 他反复推敲一个习语以使该句增色。 4. The speaker certainly knew how to turn a phrase. 该讲话者当然懂得如何措词。 5. He paused as if to find a way to phrase his next thoughts. 他顿了一下，象是在考虑接下去要说的意思该怎样来措词表达。', '形容词: phrasal 副词: phrasally 过去式: phrased 过去分词: phrased 现在分词: phrasing 第三人称单数: phrases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('helicopter', '[\'helɪkɑːptər]', 'n.直升飞机 vt.用直升飞机载送 vi.乘直升机', '1. The criminal escaped by a helicopter. 罪犯乘直升机逃走了。 2. The shipwrecked sailors were rescued by helicopter. 遭遇海难的水手已经被直升机救起。 3. We shuttled the passengers to the city center by helicopter. 我们来来回回地用直升机把旅客运送到市中心。 4. The officials were helicoptered aboard the ship. 官员们被用直升机送到船上。 5. You can helicopter to the island. 你可以乘坐直升机去那个岛。', '过去式: helicoptered 过去分词: helicoptered 现在分词: helicoptering 第三人称单数: helicopters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('along', '[ə\'lɔːŋ]', 'prep.沿着；顺着 adv.向前；一起', '1. We walked along the road. 我们沿着路走。 2. The procession passed along the street. 游行队伍沿着街道前进。 3. You can go straight along this street to the traffic light. 你可以顺着这条街一直走到红绿灯处。 4. He walked along the mountain ridge. 他顺着山脊走。 5. A small boat was drifting along. 一条小船正向前漂流着。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enlarge', '[ɪn\'lɑːrdʒ]', 'v.扩大；增大；详述', '1. I have to enlarge my vocabulary. 我必须扩大自己的词汇量。 2. I planned to enlarge this photograph. 我计划放大这张照片。 3. We must enlarge our views by reading. 我们必须以读书来增长见识。 4. I needn\'t enlarge upon this matter; you all know my views. 我不需要详述此事; 你们都知道我的意见。', '名词: enlarger 过去式: enlarged 过去分词: enlarged 现在分词: enlarging 第三人称单数: enlarges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('snap', '[snæp]', 'v.劈啪作响；崩塌；砰然关上；猛咬；谩骂；拍摄 n.啪嗒声；快照 adj.突然的；匆忙的 adv.劈啪作响地', '1. Most pine snaps as it burns. 大多数松木燃烧时都发出断裂声。 2. The violin string snapped because it was fastened too tight. 小提琴的弦上得太紧，突然断了。 3. This final misfortune caused his mind to snap. 最后这次不幸事件使他的精神一下子崩溃了。 4. The shark snapped its jaws shut. 鲨鱼啪嗒一声把嘴合上了。 5. The snap of a twig broke the silence. 一根树枝突然折断打破了寂静。 6. They carried out a snap check on the expense account. 他们对费用户口进行了突然的审查。 7. Suddenly the oar went snap. 桨突然啪的一声断了。', '过去式: snapped 过去分词: snapped 现在分词: snapping 第三人称单数: snaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spectator', '[\'spekteɪtər]', 'n.观众；旁观者', '1. Baseball is largely a spectator sport. 棒球在很大程度上是一种观众型运动。 2. Many a spectator poured down the street to the football ground. 许多观众沿街向足球场走去。 3. Hanlei looks at the world as a spectator, waiting. 韩磊以一个旁观者的身份观察世界,他善于等待。 4. It is the spectator, and not life, that art really mirrors. 艺术所真正要反映的是旁观者，而不是生活。', '形容词: spectatorial 名词: spectatorship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('code', '[koʊd]', 'n.密码；法规；准则 v.制成法典；把 ... 编码', '1. I can break the code of this box. 我能破译这个箱子的密码。 2. She tapped out in code to headquarters. 她给总部发出密码电报。 3. The Highway Code has been carried out. 公路法规已经被执行。 4. Managers are expected to comply with the company\'s code of conduct. 希望经理能够遵守公司的行为准则。 5. They coded each sample and sent them to the lab for analysis. 他们把每个样本都编了代码并送到实验室分析。', '过去式: coded 过去分词: coded 现在分词: coding 第三人称单数: codes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scan', '[skæn]', 'vt.扫描；浏览；审视；细看 vi.合韵律；划分音步 n.扫描；浏览；细看', '1. Could you teach me how to scan an image? 你可以教我如何扫描一个影像吗? 2. I scanned the newspaper when I was waiting for the bus. 等公共汽车的时候，我匆匆浏览了一下报纸。 3. She scanned his face, looking for signs of what he was thinking. 她审视他的脸,试图探寻他在思考什么。 4. I scanned my pocket for change. 我仔细查看囗袋找零钱。 5. The verses scan well. 这些诗句符合韵律。 6. The doctors gave him an ultrasonic brain scan. 医生给他做了脑部超声波扫描检查。', '形容词: scannable 名词: scanner 过去式: scanned 过去分词: scanned 现在分词: scanning 第三人称单数: scans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enclosure', '[ɪn\'kloʊʒər]', 'n.附件；围墙；围绕', '1. Please see enclosure for details. 详细资料请看附件! 2. I received your enclosure with gratitude. 附件收到, 十分感谢。 3. There are several enclosures in the envelope. 信封内装有几份附件。 4. She keeps a horse in that enclosure. 她在那个围栏里养了一匹马。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('angel', '[\'eɪndʒl]', 'n.天使；天使般的人', '1. A stunt man needs to have a good guardian angel. 当特技替身演员的得有个守护天使来保佑。 2. No sin at all is the dream of the angel. 不犯错误，那是天使的梦想。 3. She is painting an angel with outspread wings. 她正在画一个张开翅膀的天使。 4. She is lovely -- as much so as an angel. 她可爱得像个天使。', '形容词: angelic 副词: angelically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suspicion', '[sə\'spɪʃn]', 'n.猜疑；怀疑', '1. We regard her behaviour with suspicion. 我们对她的行为有怀疑。 2. \"A science fiction cannot not be regarded as a mere entertainment, but in fact it tells the reader much more.\" \"科幻小说不能简单地看成是供消遣的，而实际上它给读者展示更深刻的内容。\" 3. The talks have resulted in a lessening of suspicion. 谈话消减了彼此的怀疑。 4. His words had sowed the seeds of suspicion in their minds. 他的话已在他们心中播下怀疑的种子。', '形容词: suspicional 过去式: suspicioned 过去分词: suspicioned 现在分词: suspicioning 第三人称单数: suspicions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conspicuous', '[kən\'spɪkjuəs]', 'adj.显著的；显眼的；显而易见的', '1. Lincoln is a conspicuous example of a poor boy who succeeded. 林肯是一个穷苦孩子而功成名就的出色例子。 2. He was conspicuous for his bravery. 他因骁勇而出名。 3. A traffic sign should be conspicuous. 交通标志应该明显。 4. Notices shall be put in conspicuous places. 要保证把布告贴在显眼的地方。', '副词: conspicuously 名词: conspicuousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('budget', '[\'bʌdʒɪt]', 'n.预算 vt.编预算；为 ... 做预算 vi.节省开支 adj.廉价的；不贵的', '1. Congress has approved the new educational budget. 国会通过了新的教育预算。 2. Our budget needs drastic revision. 我们的预算需作重大修改。 3. The government has budgeted 10000000 pounds for education spending. 政府将10000000英镑编入教育预算。 4. The government plans to budget a new hospital. 政府计划在预算中拨款建一家新医院。 5. If we budget carefully, we\'ll be able to afford a new house. 如果我们精打细算就能买一座新房子了。 6. You can buy high-quality goods at budget prices there. 你可以在那买到物美价廉的商品。', '形容词: budgetary 名词: budgeter 过去式: budgeted 过去分词: budgeted 现在分词: budgeting 第三人称单数: budgets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('smile', '[smaɪl]', 'n.微笑；笑容 v.微笑；露出笑容', '1. A smile often denotes pleasure and friendship. 微笑常常表示高兴和友善。 2. Her smile makes her even more beautiful. 她的微笑使她更美丽了。 3. The most poor person in the world is the one without smile! 世界上最贫穷的人,就是没有笑容的人! 4. When they played out, there was a smile on their faces. 当他们演完时, 他们的脸上露出了笑容。 5. She smiled at me. 她向我微笑。', '形容词: smiley 副词: smilingly 名词: smiler 过去式: smiled 过去分词: smiled 现在分词: smiling 第三人称单数: smiles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ornament', '[\'ɔːrnəmənt]', 'n.装饰；装饰物 vt.装饰', '1. The palace was rich in ornament. 宫廷装饰琳琅满目。 2. The clock is simply for ornament, it doesn\'t actually work. 那时钟纯粹是为了装饰,其实不能走。 3. There is an ornament made of shells on the wall. 墙上有一个贝壳做成的装饰品。 4. We bought some ornaments for the Christmas tree. 我们买了一些装饰品来点缀圣诞树。 5. I ornamented my room with flowers. 我用鲜花装饰房间。', '名词: ornamenter 过去式: ornamented 过去分词: ornamented 现在分词: ornamenting 第三人称单数: ornaments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('twin', '[twɪn]', 'adj.孪生的；紧密联系的 n.双胞胎之一', '1. I always confounded him with his twin brother. 我总分不清他和他的孪生兄弟。 2. They are motivated by the twin goads of punishment and reward. 他们受赏与罚的双重因素所激励。 3. I can\'t tell one twin from the other. 我分不出双胞胎中谁是谁。', '过去式: twinned 过去分词: twinned 现在分词: twinning 第三人称单数: twins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('realistic', '[ˌriːə\'lɪstɪk]', 'adj.现实的；现实主义的', '1. He was realistic about difficulties. 他对困难持现实的态度。 2. We should encourage pupils to set realistic goals. 我们要鼓励学生设定现实的目标。 3. This is a realistic novel about ghetto life. 这是一部描写贫民窟的现实主义小说。 4. The great majority are realistic politicians. 绝大多数是现实主义的政治家。', '副词: realistically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('proceed', '[proʊ\'siːd]', 'vi.继续进行；开始；着手', '1. We received sanction to proceed with our plans. 我们获准继续进行我们的计划。 2. Please go upstairs and proceed through the security check and immigration. 请您到楼上继续进行安全检查和移民检查。 3. Please proceed with your presentation. 请开始你的简报。 4. After everyone was seated the chairman proceeded to announce his plan. 大家就坐后，主席开始宣布他的计划。', '名词: proceeder 过去式: proceeded 过去分词: proceeded 现在分词: proceeding 第三人称单数: proceeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scheme', '[skiːm]', 'n.阴谋；计划；方案 v.图谋；设计；策划；<非正式>认为', '1. Their scheme was exposed. 他们的阴谋被暴露了。 2. The police have uncovered a scheme of robbery. 警察当局破获了一起阴谋抢劫案。 3. They were bitterly opposed to the scheme. 他们强烈反对这个计划。 4. I rather doubt if such an ambitious scheme could be made a success of. 我真怀疑这样一个雄心勃勃的计划是否会成功。 5. He is scheming for power. 他在图谋争权。', '名词: schemer 过去式: schemed 过去分词: schemed 现在分词: scheming 第三人称单数: schemes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('core', '[kɔːr]', 'n.核心；果心；要点 vt.挖去果核', '1. The core of our appeal is freedom of speech. 我们的要求的核心是言论自由。 2. He is American to the core. 他是个地地道道的美国人。 3. He ate the plum, and threw the core away. 他吃掉了李子，并扔掉了果核。 4. Let\'s get to the core of the argument. 咱们进入实质性的辩论吧。', '过去式: cored 过去分词: cored 现在分词: coring 第三人称单数: cores');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accompany', '[ə\'kʌmpəni]', 'vt.陪伴；伴随...发生；补充；给 ... 伴奏 vi.伴奏', '1. She asked me to accompany her to the airport. 她要求我陪她到机场去。 2. Lightning usually accompanies thunder. 闪电通常伴有雷声。 3. The text is accompanied by illustration. 正文附有插图。 4. The singer was accompanied on the piano by her sister. 女歌手由她姐姐钢琴伴奏。 5. In the singer\'s eyes,she accompanied magnificently. 在那名歌手的眼里,她伴奏得精彩极了。', '过去式: accompanied 过去分词: accompanied 现在分词: accompanying 第三人称单数: accompanies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bid', '[bɪd]', 'v.（买方）出价；投标；吩咐；叫牌 n.出价；努力；叫牌', '1. She bid 500 for the painting. 她喊价500买这幅画。 2. Several firms have bid for the contract to build the new concert hall. 有几家公司投标，争取建造新音乐厅的合同。 3. Several companies are bidding for the contract to build the bridge. 有几家公司在投标争取承包建桥工程。 4. Do as you are bidden. 按照吩咐你的去做。 5. He made a bid of 50 for a painting. 他为一幅画出价50英镑。', '名词: bidder 过去式: bade/bid 过去分词: bidden/bid 现在分词: bidding 第三人称单数: bids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consistent', '[kən\'sɪstənt]', 'adj.始终如一的；持续的；一致的', '1. She is a consistent girl in her feeling. 在感情方面她是个始终如一的女孩。 2. Our aim is to ensure a consistent growth. 我们的目标是确保持续的增长。 3. Your conduct is not consistent with what you say. 你的言行不一致。', '副词: consistently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stagger', '[\'stæɡər]', 'vi.蹒跚；犹豫；动摇 vt.使摇晃；使吃惊；使犹豫 n.蹒跚；踌躇；摇摆不定', '1. She staggered and fell. 她踉跄了几步，跌倒在地。 2. The drunk man staggered across the room. 那个醉汉摇摇晃晃地穿过房间。 3. His resolution had begun to stagger. 他的意志开始动摇了。 4. Such a heavy load would stagger an elephant. 这么重的担子，大象担着也得摇晃。 5. He gave a stagger on hearing the news. 他听到这一消息两腿摇晃起来。', '形容词: staggery 名词: staggerer 过去式: staggered 过去分词: staggered 现在分词: staggering 第三人称单数: staggers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clay', '[kleɪ]', 'n.黏土；泥土', '1. Clay is a plastic substance. 黏土是可塑物质。 2. Clay soil retains water. 黏土能保持水分。 3. Bricks and dishes are made from various kinds of clay. 砖和盘子由各种粘土制成。 4. It was said that the first man was moulded from clay by some kind of god. 据传，第一个人是某个神用泥土造出来的。', '形容词: clayey');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soon', '[suːn]', 'adv.不久；很快；早；快', '1. I\'ll be back soon. 我马上回来。 2. She will be here sooner than you expect. 她很快就到，比你预料的要早。 3. He left as soon as he heard the news. 他一听到这事儿就走了。 4. The detective soon raveled out the truth. 那名侦探很快就于真相大白。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('foreigner', '[\'fɔːrənər]', 'n.外国人；外人', '1. She wedded a foreigner. 她嫁给了一个外国人。 2. The foreigner knew the local custom very well. 这位外国人对当地的风俗非常熟悉。 3. His accent argues him to be a foreigner. 他的腔调表明他是个外国人。 4. \"Those who live in my house and my maids consider me a stranger. I am a foreigner in their sight. 在我家寄居的、和我的使女、都以我为外人．我在他们眼中看为外邦人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('argument', '[\'ɑːrɡjumənt]', 'n.辩论；论点；论据；争论；理由；(函数)自变量', '1. She handled a difficult argument skilfully. 她巧妙地应付了一场艰难的辩论。 2. This argument, however, does not hold water. 但是,这种观点是站不住脚的。 3. This point is vital to my argument. 这一点对我的论据极为重要。 4. We accepted the agreement without argument. 我们毫无异议地接受了这一协议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drink', '[drɪŋk]', 'v.喝；饮 n.饮料；酒；喝酒', '1. It is harmful to your health to drink too much. 过量喝酒对你的身体有害。 2. It\'s not good to drink on an empty stomach. 空腹喝酒不好。 3. Let us drink to the health of our father. 让我们举杯为父亲祝福。 4. The deer lowered its head to drink from the pond. 鹿低下头去喝池塘里的水。 5. Cold tea makes an excellent drink in summer. 在夏天，凉茶是一种很好的饮料。', '过去式: drank 过去分词: drunk 现在分词: drinking 第三人称单数: drinks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('herself', '[hɜːr\'self]', 'pron.她自己；她亲自', '1. She kept on muttering to herself. 她老是一个人嘀嘀咕咕。 2. She braided her hair by herself. 她自己梳辫子。 3. After her swim she dried herself with a towel. 游泳后，她用毛巾擦干身子。 4. She should do her homework herself. 她应该自己做作业。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('failure', '[\'feɪljər]', 'n.失败；失败者；不及格；疏忽；失灵；未能；悲惨的事', '1. I shall have another chance in the event of failure. 如果失败，我还有另一个机会。 2. The play was a dead failure. 这场戏完全失败了。 3. I was a failure in my own eyes. 在我眼里,我是个失败者。 4. In a word, his failure in the final exam did not surprise me. 总而言之,他考试不及格并没使我吃惊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('swarm', '[swɔːrm]', 'n.群；蜂群 v.云集；充满', '1. I saw a swarm of bees attacking the poor monkey. 我看到一群蜜蜂正在攻击可怜的猴子。 2. He has received a swarm of letters. 他已经收到了一大批信件。 3. The locust swarm has destroyed all the crops and vegetables. 蝗虫群毁坏了所有的庄稼和蔬菜。 4. Like bees in a swarm, these stars move on ever changing orbits. 好比蜂群内的蜜蜂那般，球状星团内的恒星运行在不断变化的轨道之上。 5. Many students swarm into the canteen after class. 放学后,很多学生拥进食堂。', '名词: swarmer 过去式: swarmed 过去分词: swarmed 现在分词: swarming 第三人称单数: swarms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forward', '[\'fɔːrwərd]', 'adj.向前的；前部的；未来的；将来的；莽撞的；热心的；早熟的 adv.向前地 v.促进；转交；发送 n.[体]前锋', '1. He is forward in his English. 他的英语有进步。 2. We can see the forward part of the ship. 我们可以看见船的前部。 3. A little forward planning at the outset can save you a lot of expense. 一开始就为未来作点打算能节约很多开支。 4. I hope you\'ll apologize that was a very forward thing to do. 我希望你能道歉－－那事你做得太莽撞了。 5. She stepped forward in order to see clearly. 她向前走了一步以便能看得更清楚 6. He\'s hoping to forward his career by this move. 他正希望通过这一举动来促进他的事业。 7. The forward made a foul in the penalty area. 前锋在禁区内犯规了。', '副词: forwardly 名词: forwardness 过去式: forwarded 过去分词: forwarded 现在分词: forwarding 第三人称单数: forwards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suburb', '[\'sʌbɜːrb]', 'n.郊区', '1. They proposed setting up a school in the suburb. 他们建议在这个郊区成立一所学校。 2. The factory is located in the suburb. 那家工厂坐落于郊区。 3. Ronaldo grew up in Bento Ribeiro, a suburb of Rio. 罗纳尔多在里约热内卢的一个叫本托. 4. Do not you think it would be nice to live in the suburb? 难道你不认为住在郊区是件好事吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('color', '[\'kʌlər]', 'n.颜色；彩色；颜料 vt.渲染；把 ... 涂颜色 vi.脸红；着色；影响，左右 =colour（英）', '1. That\'s rather an effective use of color. 这种使用颜色的手法效果相当好。 2. This is a sort of indeterminate color. 这是一种说不清的颜色。 3. Pink is her favorite color. 粉红色是她最喜欢的颜色。 4. It has been desired to obtain a single color film. 人们希望得到一种简单的彩色胶片。 5. I\'d like you to color the place up a bit. 我希望你把这地方装得鲜艳一些。 6. She felt the color flamed up in her cheek. 她感到自己的脸红了。', '名词: colorer 过去式: colored 过去分词: colored 现在分词: coloring 第三人称单数: colors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('if', '[ɪf]', 'conj.是否；如果；即使；每当 n.条件；设想', '1. Do you know if he\'s married? 他结婚没结婚，你知道吗？ 2. I can give you a round neckline if you prefer. 如果您喜欢我可以给您开个圆领口。 3. If he wins and it\'s a big if he\'ll be the first Englishman to win for twenty years. 假使他赢了－－是否能赢还是一大疑问－－他将是二十年来第一个获胜的英国人。 4. She glares at me if I go near her desk. 我一走近她的办公桌，她就瞪我。 5. Why not,if the conditions permit. 如果条件允许，没什么不可以的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('powerful', '[\'paʊərfl]', 'adj.强有力的；强大的；有权的；强健的', '1. This defeat was a powerful blow to the enemy. 这次失败是对敌人的有力的打击。 2. The elephant grinds its food with its powerful molars. 象用其强有力的臼齿嚼碎食物。 3. Russia used to be a very powerful country. 俄国曾是一个非常强大的国家。 4. The chancellor is the most powerful man in the Austrian government. 首相是奥地利政府最有实权的人。', '副词: powerfully 名词: powerfulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grim', '[ɡrɪm]', 'adj.严厉的；冷酷的；可怕的；不愉快的', '1. Her face wore a grim, set look. 她脸上显出严厉、 木然的神情。 2. His expression was grim when he told them they had lost their job. 当他告诉他们说他们已被解雇时，他的表情十分冷酷。 3. A grim and unsightly picture met his eye. 一幅可怕和难看的情景映入他的眼帘。 4. I had a pretty grim day yesterday. 我昨天很不愉快。', '副词: grimly 比较级: grimmer 最高级: grimmest 名词: grimness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oak', '[oʊk]', 'n.橡树；橡木', '1. The birds nested in the oak tree. 鸟在橡树上筑巢。 2. Pine wood saws more easily than oak. 松树要比橡树容易锯。 3. The wine is left to mature in oak barrels. 葡萄酒在橡木桶中陈酿。 4. There was a triptych of pale oak. 有一个浅灰色的三联橡木雕刻。', '形容词: oaken');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mostly', '[\'moʊstli]', 'adv.主要地；通常', '1. Recycled materials are mostly of limited use. 再生材料大多用途有限。 2. He reads the occasional book, but mostly just magazines. 他偶尔也看书，但大多只看杂志。 3. Lizards live mostly in warm climates. 蜥蜴主要生长在气候温暖的地方。 4. He works mostly in London office. 他通常在伦敦办事处工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tray', '[treɪ]', 'n.托盘；盘', '1. Put the tray over there. 把托盘放到那边去。 2. He put the toast on the breakfast tray. 他把烤面包片放到早餐托盘里。 3. I tripped over, dropping the tray I was carrying. 我绊了一下，手中的托盘掉在地上了。 4. Letters were piled high in the tray on his desk. 他办公桌上的文件盘里有很多信。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unit', '[\'juːnɪt]', 'n.单元；单位；部件；组件', '1. This textbook has twenty units. 这本课本有二十单元。 2. There\'s a rumour floating around of a new job in the unit. 这个部门盛传有个新工作要聘人。 3. The family is the smallest social unit. 家庭是社会最小的单位。 4. Cubit is an ancient unit of length. 腕尺是古代的一种长度单位。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deputy', '[\'depjuti]', 'n.代表；副手；议员', '1. My younger brother is my deputy during my absence. 我不在时，我弟弟代表我。 2. He is a deputy to the National People\'s Congress. 他是人民代表大会代表。 3. I must find someone to act as a deputy for me during my absence. 我必须找一个人，在我离开期间代理我的职务。 4. I am resigning as chairman and handing over to my deputy. 我现在辞去主席职位，交由我的副手接替。', '名词复数: deputies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('correspond', '[ˌkɔːrə\'spɑːnd]', 'v.符合；对应；通信', '1. Your account and hers correspond. 你的说法跟她的说法一致。 2. Your account of events corresponds with hers. 你说的情况跟她说的相符。 3. The American Congress corresponds to the British Parliament. 美国的国会相当于英国的议会。 4. I correspond with him regularly. 我经常和他通信。', '过去式: corresponded 过去分词: corresponded 现在分词: corresponding 第三人称单数: corresponds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('generate', '[\'dʒenəreɪt]', 'vt.产生；发生；引起', '1. 75% of France\'s electricity is generated by nuclear reactors. 法国75%25的电能产生于核反应堆。 2. We can\'t generate enough power for the entire city. 我们不能为整个城市产生足够的能量。 3. We need someone to generate new ideas. 我们需要有人出新主意。 4. This hatred was generated by racial prejudice. 这种仇恨是由种族偏见引起的。', '过去式: generated 过去分词: generated 现在分词: generating 第三人称单数: generates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gigantic', '[dʒaɪ\'ɡæntɪk]', 'adj.巨大的', '1. The new airplane looked like a gigantic bird. 这架新飞机看起来像一只巨大的鸟。 2. City is abstracted into several gigantic buildings. 城市，被抽象化为几个巨大的建筑物。', '副词: gigantically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inch', '[ɪntʃ]', 'n.英寸；少量 v.慢慢移动 （复）inches: 身高.', '1. She shortened the shirt by an inch. 她把衬衫截短了一英寸。 2. The candle grew down until only an inch was left. 蜡烛越来越短,最后只剩下一英寸了。 3. There was an inch of snow on the ground. 地上积着一英寸厚的白雪。 4. They climbed the steep mountain inch by inch. 他们一点一点地攀上那座陡峭的山。 5. Prices are inching down. 物价在慢慢下降。 6. His legs are too long for his inches. 就他的身高而言，他的腿太长了。', '过去式: inched 过去分词: inched 现在分词: inching 第三人称单数: inches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('parade', '[pə\'reɪd]', 'n.游行；检阅；游行地 vi.参加游行；阅兵；散步；炫耀 vt.夸耀；使参加游行；检阅；绕行', '1. People wore historical costumes for the parade. 人们穿著古装参加游行。 2. The children flew out to see the parade. 孩子们奔出去看游行队伍。 3. No words can express the grandeur of that parade. 阅兵式那宏伟的场面是无法用语言表达的。 4. The general inspected the parade. 将军检阅了阅兵式。 5. The strikers paraded through the city center. 罢工队伍游行穿过市中心。 6. He is always parading his knowledge. 他总是夸耀自己的知识。', '名词: parader 过去式: paraded 过去分词: paraded 现在分词: parading 第三人称单数: parades');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recipe', '[\'resəpi]', 'n.秘诀；食谱；药方', '1. What\'s your recipe for success? 你取得成功有什么窍门？ 2. He knows the recipe for this dish. 他知道这道菜的烹饪方法。 3. This recipe will be enough for four servings. 本食谱为四人食用分量。 4. In fact, could I ask you for the recipe? 事实上,我能向你要这道菜的食谱吗?', '名词复数: recipes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appendix', '[ə\'pendɪks]', 'n.附录；附属物；阑尾', '1. There is an appendix at the back of the book. 该书末尾处有一附录。 2. This is the appendix to the investigation report. 这是调查报告的附件。 3. The details are clearly set out in an appendix. 详细情况在一个附录里清楚列出。 4. He had his appendix taken out. 他的阑尾割去了。', '名词复数: appendixes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discriminate', '[dɪ\'skrɪmɪneɪt]', 'vt.区分；区别对待 vi.辨别；差别对待', '1. You must learn to discriminate fact from opinion. 你必须学会把事实和看法区分开。 2. Can you discriminate good books from bad? 你能区别好书与坏书吗？ 3. Death does not discriminate; it comes to everyone. 死亡对每个人都一视同仁，它会降临到每个人的身上。 4. He is able to discriminate good book from bad. 他具有区分优秀图书与低劣图书的能力。 5. You must learn to discriminate between things. 你必须学会区别事物。', '副词: discriminately 过去式: discriminated 过去分词: discriminated 现在分词: discriminating 第三人称单数: discriminates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('farther', '[\'fɑːrðər]', 'adj.更远的；较远的 adv.更远地；进一步地', '1. The farther hill is five kilometres away. 那座更远的小山在五公里以外。 2. The nearer the church, the farther from God. 离教堂越近,离上帝越远。 3. On the farther side of the street there was a row of small shops. 街那头是一排小商店。 4. We can\'t go any farther without a rest. 不休息我们就走不动了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('window', '[\'wɪndoʊ]', 'n.窗户；橱窗；视窗', '1. The fresh air blew in from the open window. 新鲜空气从开着的窗户吹进来。 2. Snowflakes were patting against the window. 雪花轻轻拍打着窗户。 3. He looked out of the window. 他向窗外看去。 4. I saw the vase in the window of an antique shop. 我在一家古玩店的橱窗里看见了那个花瓶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cohesive', '[koʊ\'hiːsɪv]', 'adj.粘性的；有结合性的；有粘聚性的', '1. I would use a cohesive glue to weld the tubes to each other. 我会用粘胶把这些电子管粘起来。 2. He skillfully fuses these fragments into a cohesive whole. 他巧妙地把这些片断合并成连贯的整体。 3. They do not see themselves as a cohesive group. 他们不认为他们自己是有凝聚力的一群。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('physician', '[fɪ\'zɪʃn]', 'n.内科医生', '1. He was attended by his personal physician. 他的私人医生护理他。 2. He prefers to be a surgeon rather than a physician. 他喜欢当外科医生而不愿作内科医生。 3. The physician put him on a special diet. 内科医生给他吃特定的食物。 4. He consulted his physician about his health. 他请医生诊断他的健康。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mutter', '[\'mʌtər]', 'v.咕哝；抱怨；低语 n.嘟哝；抱怨；低语', '1. Mutter Sarah was muttering away to herself as she did the washing-up. 萨拉一边洗碗碟一边独自咕哝个没完。 2. Some members of the government are beginning to mutter about the prime minister. 一些政府官员开始咕咕哝哝地抱怨首相。 3. Some members of the government are beginning to mutter about the prime minister. 一些政府官员开始咕咕哝哝地抱怨首相。 4. Don\'t mutter when they are studying. 当他们学习时不要轻声低语。 5. Some members of the government are beginning to mutter about the prime minister. 一些政府官员开始咕咕哝哝地抱怨首相。', '名词: mutterer 过去式: muttered 过去分词: muttered 现在分词: muttering 第三人称单数: mutters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('imitate', '[\'ɪmɪteɪt]', 'vt.仿效；仿制；模仿', '1. You should imitate great and good people. 你应仿效伟大善良的人。 2. Teachers provide a model for children to imitate. 教师是孩子们仿效的典范。 3. People imitate diamonds with crystal. 人们用水晶仿造钻石。 4. He can imitate his teacher perfectly. 他能维妙维肖地模仿他的老师。', '名词: imitator 过去式: imitated 过去分词: imitated 现在分词: imitating 第三人称单数: imitates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stadium', '[\'steɪdiəm]', 'n.体育场；运动场；[生]期', '1. The crowds drifted away from the stadium. 人群慢慢从体育场散去。 2. Keep on past the church; the stadium is about half a mile further on. 一直向前走过了教堂，约莫半英里就是体育场。 3. We will go to the stadium to watch a football match. 我们将去体育场观看足球比赛。 4. The takings at the football stadium has fallen off. 足球运动场的收入减少了。', '名词复数: stadiums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('electronic', '[ɪˌlek\'trɑːnɪk]', 'adj.电子的；电子学的', '1. This dictionary is available in electronic version. 这部词典有电子版。 2. I like to read books on electronic music. 我喜欢读一些关于电子音乐的书。 3. Helen became an electronic engineer. 海伦成了一名电子工程师。', '副词: electronically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lock', '[lɑːk]', 'n.锁；水闸；一缕头发；一簇；一束 v.固定；锁(住)；抓牢；过闸', '1. He chiseled a hole in the door to fit a new lock. 他在门上凿了个孔，以便装一把新锁。 2. Water went rushing through the lock gates. 水流经水闸时十分湍急。 3. He keeps a lock of her hair. 他保存着她的一绺头发。 4. The ship was locked in the ice through the winter. 整个冬天船只被冻在冰层里。', '形容词: lockable 过去式: locked 过去分词: locked 现在分词: locking 第三人称单数: locks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blueprint', '[\'bluːprɪnt]', 'n.蓝图；设计图；(周详的)计划 v.制成蓝图；计划', '1. There is a slight inaccuracy in this blueprint. 这张蓝图有点不准。 2. To receive this new blueprint, one must ask for it. 要去接收到这个新蓝图，你必须召唤它。 3. You have a perfect blueprint about your life. 人生计划已很完美。 4. Ascending human futures have a Divine Plan, a divine blueprint. 提升人类的未来有一个神性计划，一个神性蓝图。 5. You have a perfect blueprint about your life. 人生计划已很完美。', '过去式: blueprinted 过去分词: blueprinted 现在分词: blueprinting 第三人称单数: blueprints');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grind', '[ɡraɪnd]', 'v.磨；压迫；碾碎；磨得吱吱响；逐渐停顿 n.苦事；磨；碾', '1. It won\'t grind down any finer than this. 不能磨得比这个再细了。 2. Some people grind their teeth while they are asleep. 有些人睡觉时磨牙齿。 3. People in this area were ground down by hunger and poverty. 这个地区的人们受着饥饿和贫穷的折磨。 4. We grind up the wheat to make flour. 我们把小麦磨成面粉。 5. Marking examination papers is a real grind. 批改试卷的确是个苦事。', '副词: grindingly 过去式: ground 过去分词: ground 现在分词: grinding 第三人称单数: grinds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('setting', '[\'setɪŋ]', 'n.背景；环境；镶嵌；安装；放置；（日月的）沉落；[音]乐曲 动词set的现在分词形式.', '1. Our story has its setting in ancient Rome. 我们这个故事的背景是在古罗马。 2. An informal work setting helps to build employee enthusiasm and morale. 不拘形式的工作环境，提高了员工的热情与士气。 3. She liked the diamond itself but not the setting. 她喜欢那颗钻石，但不喜欢它的镶嵌底座。 4. We are setting up a printing press. 我们正在安装一台印刷机。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impress', '[ɪm\'pres]', 'n.印记；印象；特征 v.使 ... 有印象；影响；印刻；传送', '1. Their honesty and hospitality leave an indelible impress on her life. 他们的诚实与好客给她一生留下了难以磨灭的印象。 2. I had a chance to impress her with my efficiency and I muffed it up. 我本来有机会使她对我的办事效率有印象,但是我错过了这个机会。 3. She impressed me as a scholar. 她给我留下了学者的印象。 4. What impress you most when you go to IKEA? 您去宜家时以下哪一项对您影响最深刻？', '过去式: impressed 过去分词: impressed 现在分词: impressing 第三人称单数: impresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('practise', '[\'præktɪs]', 'v.练习；实践；实行；开业 n.练习；实践；实行；业务；惯例 =practice.', '1. I need to practise my Italian before my business trip. 我出差之前需要先练习一下意大利语。 2. I strive to practise these two virtues in my life. 我在生活中努力实践这两种美德。 3. For the present, we have to practise the supply system of distribution. 现在我们也只能实行供给制。 4. The majority of judgers are barrister, but they cannot practise as barrister. 多数法官是高级律师，但他们不能作为高级律师开业。 5. Lots of practise is necessary for well-learning english . 要学好英语，大量的练习是必要的。', '名词: practiser');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cautious', '[\'kɔːʃəs]', 'adj.谨慎的；十分小心的', '1. She is cautious of telling secrets. 她很谨慎，不会泄露秘密。 2. He is cautious in his choice of words. 他措辞很谨慎。 3. They\'ve taken a very cautious approach. 他们采取了十分谨慎的态度。 4. The old lady is very cautious with money. 那位老太太用钱很谨慎。', '副词: cautiously 名词: cautiousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ourselves', '[ɑːr\'selvz]', 'pron.我们自己', '1. We have a bathroom to ourselves. 我们自己有一间浴室，不必和人共用。 2. No one can degrade us except ourselves. 除了我们自己，没有人能贬低我们。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('downward', '[\'daʊnwərd]', 'adv.向下 adj.向下的；下降的', '1. She laid the picture face downward on the table. 她把那幅画正面朝下放在桌上。 2. The bird glided downward and rested in the grass. 这只鸟向下滑翔，降落在草丛里。 3. The custom has continued from the 16th century downward. 这种风俗自十六世纪沿袭下来。 4. He is on the downward path. 他正在走下坡路。', '副词: downwardly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('realise', '[\'rɪəlaɪz]', 'v.<英>意识到；实现；明白；变现 =realize', '1. He didn\'t realise how late it was. 他并没有意识到已经有多晚了。 2. You were acting like you didn\'t realise that. 看起来好象你没意识到那点。 3. Many a parent pins the hopes on the children to realise their unfilled ambitions. 很多父母试图在他们的儿女身上实现他们的梦想。 4. You broke the promise and made me realise. 你带走了承诺让我明白。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('curtain', '[\'kɜːrtn]', 'n.窗帘；门帘；幕(布) vt.(用帘)装饰；(以帘)遮蔽', '1. The curtain was suddenly drawn and a bright light shone in. 突然窗帘拉了开来，一道强光照了进来。 2. She came upon a low curtain she had not noticed before. 她发现刚才没有注意到的一个低垂的门帘。 3. She kept peering through the side curtain. 她不时地从旁边的幕帐向外窥视。 4. The curtain rose to disclose a stunning set. 布帘被揭开暴露出极好的布。 5. I bought enough material to curtain the house. 我买了不少布料，足够做房子的窗帘用。', '过去式: curtained 过去分词: curtained 现在分词: curtaining 第三人称单数: curtains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('owl', '[aʊl]', 'n.猫头鹰', '1. The owl swooped down on the mouse. 那只猫头鹰向着老鼠猛扑下来。 2. The owl hunts while you repose in bed. 你躺在床上安然入睡时，猫头鹰却要去觅食。 3. The hooting of an owl broke the silence now and again, giving Linda the creeps. 猫头鹰的叫声不时打破寂静，使琳达心惊肉跳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quit', '[kwɪt]', 'v.停止；离开；退出；辞职', '1. You must quit smoking. Most important of all, you should start taking exercise. 你必须戒烟，更重要的是，你该开始运动。 2. They have to quit China in a few days. 他们必须在几天之内离开中国。 3. The guard did not quit his post all night long. 那个哨兵整夜都没有离开他的哨位。 4. Some students quit school due to poverty. 一些学生因贫困而辍学。', '过去式: quit/quitted 过去分词: quit/quitted 现在分词: quitting 第三人称单数: quits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nickel', '[\'nɪkl]', 'n.镍；镍币；五分镍币 vt.镀镍于', '1. Danish women have contact allergy caused by nickel. 丹麦妇女因镍造成接触性过敏症。 2. Bear ran over to Pig and bought another hot dog with the nickel. 熊跑到猪那，用这个五分镍币从猪那买了一个热狗。 3. America\'s best buy for a nickel is a telephone call to the right man. 在美国以一枚镍币可购得的最划算的东西，是打电话找到要找的人。 4. Each nickel is worth five cents. 每个五分镍币相当于5美分。 5. Screw plugs, brass nickel plated, with metric thread. 圆形螺旋塞，材质为黄铜镀镍，公制螺纹。', '过去式: nickeled/nickelled 过去分词: nickeled/nickelled 现在分词: nickeling/nickelling 第三人称单数: nickels/nickels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('agriculture', '[\'æɡrɪkʌltʃər]', 'n.农业；农学；农艺', '1. I know nothing about agriculture. 我对农业一窍不通。 2. Modern agriculture is spoiling our beautiful countryside. 现代农业正在破坏我们美丽的农村。 3. Agriculture in this country has developed greatly after liberation. 解放后这个国家的农业得到了巨大的发展。 4. He studied agriculture in college. 他在大学里研究农学。', '形容词: agricultural 副词: agriculturally 名词: agriculturist');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sister', '[\'sɪstər]', 'n.姐妹', '1. Joan and Lily are sisters. 琼和丽丽是姐妹。 2. You should take care of your niece for the sake of your sister. 看在姐妹的份上，你应该照顾你的侄女。 3. She looks nothing like her sister. 她一点也不像她姐妹', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discreet', '[dɪ\'skriːt]', 'adj.谨慎的；不引人注意的；朴素的，简易的', '1. It was not discreet of you to say that. 你那样说有欠考虑。 2. Be more discreet or you\'ll get yourself talked about. 要更谨慎些－－否则你就会成为人们的话柄。 3. I\'ll certainly be most discreet in my conversation. 我在谈话中当然会十分小心的。 4. It was a discreet apartment in a quiet street. 那是间位於一条僻静的街上不引人注意的公寓房间。', '副词: discreetly 名词: discreetness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rat', '[ræt]', 'n.变节者；鼠；卑鄙的人 v.捕鼠；背叛；偷窃', '1. He was regarded as a rat. 大家叫他变节者/叛徒。 2. The dog was worrying a rat. 那条狗撕咬著一只老鼠。 3. The dog nosed out a rat. 那只狗闻到了老鼠的气味。 4. Now I can see why people say he is such a rat. 现在我知道了为什么人们说他是卑鄙小人了。 5. The little boy likes to rat. 这个小男孩喜欢捕鼠。', '过去式: ratted 过去分词: ratted 现在分词: ratting 第三人称单数: rats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appropriate', '[ə\'proʊpriət]', 'adj.适当的；相称的 vt.占用；拨出(款项)', '1. You will be informed of the details at the appropriate time. 在适当的时候将把详情告诉你。 2. It is not easy to choose clothes which are appropriate to your beautiful figure. 选择与你漂亮的体型相称的服装是不容易的。 3. She again entreated his forgiveness for so selfishly appropriating the cottage 她为自己这么自私地占用了这座农舍而再次恳求他的原谅。 4. The government has appropriated some funds for education. 政府拨出了一些款项用作教育基金。', '形容词: appropriative 副词: appropriately 名词: appropriateness 过去式: appropriated 过去分词: appropriated 现在分词: appropriating 第三人称单数: appropriates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sham', '[ʃæm]', 'n.假；赝品；骗子；枕头套 adj.假的；伪造的 v.假装；学样子', '1. His love was a sham; he only wanted her money. 他爱她是假的，他只想要她的钱。 2. She claims to know all about computers but really she\'s a sham. 她自称精通计算机，其实她是假充内行。 3. Are these real diamonds or only sham? 这些是真的钻石还是赝品? 4. He a man! Hell! He was a hollow sham. 他是男子汉？见鬼！他是个虚伪的骗子。 5. They cunningly played the game of sham peace. 他们狡滑地玩弄假和平的把戏。 6. He\'s only shamming. 他只是假装而已。', '名词: shammer 过去式: shammed 过去分词: shammed 现在分词: shamming 第三人称单数: shams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diligent', '[\'dɪlɪdʒənt]', 'adj.勤奋的；用功的', '1. The diligent student gets up before dawn every day. 这个勤奋的学生每天天亮以前就起床了。 2. Their students are diligent about their studies. 他们的学生勤奋学习。 3. She is more diligent than any other students in her class. 她是班上最用功的学生。', '副词: diligently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('price', '[praɪs]', 'n.价格；代价；价值 v.给…定价；估价；贴价格标签；比较价格', '1. I wonder why the company keeps its price so low. 我奇怪那个公司为什么把他们的价格压得那么低。 2. No price is too high for winning their support. 为了获得他们的支持，任何代价均在所不惜。 3. It will be cheap at the price if this tour can keep the whole family happy. 只要这次旅游能让全家人开心,再贵也值得了。 4. I\'ll ask an expert to price the old car. 我将请一位专家来给这辆旧车定价。', '形容词: priceable 名词: pricer 过去式: priced 过去分词: priced 现在分词: pricing 第三人称单数: prices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('melon', '[\'melən]', 'n.甜瓜', '1. We garnished the melon with strawberries. 我们给甜瓜配上草莓。 2. Saya mempunyai sebuah Kiwi dan sebuah Melon. 我有一个猕猴桃和一个甜瓜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('serious', '[\'sɪriəs]', 'adj.严肃的；严重的；认真的；危急的；庄重的', '1. Do not treat this serious matter as a joke. 不要把这件严肃的事情当作笑料。 2. A serious look passed over his face. 他脸上显出一副严肃的神色。 3. There was a serious motor smash on the bridge. 桥上发生了严重的汽车相撞事故。 4. We are today facing a serious credit crunch. 我们今日正面对严重的信贷困难。', '副词: seriously 名词: seriousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('musician', '[mju\'zɪʃn]', 'n.音乐家', '1. That musician is very famous. 那位音乐家非常有名。 2. He\'s not in the first grade as a musician. 他不是第一流的音乐家。 3. The musician made the legend into a beautiful ballad. 这位音乐家把传说编成了一首美丽的民谣。 4. She is a talented musician as well as being a photographer. 她不但是摄影师还是个天才的音乐家。', '形容词: musicianly 名词: musicianship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('democracy', '[dɪ\'mɑːkrəsi]', 'n.民主国家；民主；民主制', '1. Greece must have a system if it is to become a self supporting and self respecting democracy. 要想成为一个自立、自尊的民主国家，希腊必须有一个健全的体制。 2. The election demonstrates democracy in action. 这次选举是以实际行动体现了民主。 3. Democracy is a bulwark of freedom. 民主是自由的保障。 4. The military government promised to restore democracy within one year. 军人政府答应在一年内重新建立民主体制。', '名词复数: democracies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anecdote', '[\'ænɪkdoʊt]', 'n.轶事；奇闻', '1. He departs from the text to tell an anecdote. 他没讲课文而讲了一段轶事。 2. He preceded his lecture with a humorous anecdote. 他以一个幽默的轶事开始他的演说 3. He told me some anecdotes about our English teacher. 他告诉我几个关于英语老师的掌故。 4. It had never been more than a family anecdote. 那不过是个家庭趣谈罢了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interest', '[\'ɪntrəst]', 'n.兴趣；嗜好；利息；股份 v.使…感兴趣', '1. He showed not a spark of interest in the plan. 他对这个计划一点不感兴趣。 2. His two great interests in life are music and painting. 音乐和绘画是他生活中的两大嗜好。 3. Do you pay interest on that account? 那种存款付给利息吗? 4. He has an interest in the company. 他在这家公司拥有股份。 5. Things of that nature do not interest me. 我对那种事物不感兴趣。', '过去式: interested 过去分词: interested 现在分词: interesting 第三人称单数: interests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('apparatus', '[ˌæpə\'rætəs]', 'n.器官；装置；机构；组织；仪器', '1. The bird has specialized vocal apparatus. 这只鸟有特殊的发音器官。 2. The demonstrators set up apparatus for the experiment. 示范者安装好了实验装置。 3. The whole apparatus operates under high vacuum. 整个装置在高真空下运转。 4. The city\'s security apparatus needs reforming. 这个城市的治安机构需要改良。', '名词复数: apparatus');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('centimetre', '[\'sentɪmiːtər]', 'n.厘米 =centimeter（美）', '1. Round each measurement to the nearest whole inch or centimetre. 将每个测量数目四舍五入到最近的英寸或厘米整数。', '名词复数: centimetres');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exchange', '[ɪks\'tʃeɪndʒ]', 'v.交换；兑换 n.交换；交易所；兑换；交战', '1. May I exchange seats with you? 我和你调一个座位好吗? 2. You can exchange your car at our nearest office. 你可以到我们附近的公司换车。 3. We exchanged our opinions about the event at the meeting. 在会上，我们就此事交换了意见。 4. I\'d like to exchange some pounds for dollars. 我想把一些英镑兑换成美金。 5. He gave me an apple in exchange of an orange. 他给我一个苹果，交换一个橙子。', '形容词: exchangeable 过去式: exchanged 过去分词: exchanged 现在分词: exchanging 第三人称单数: exchanges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('self', '[self]', 'n.自己；本性；自我 pron.我自己；你自己；他或她自己 adj.始终如一的；同一类型的；性质不变的 v.近亲繁殖；自花授粉', '1. He is now out of all conceit with his former self. 他现在全盘否定了他原来的自己。 2. I do not like to go to the movies by my self. 我不喜欢自己一个人看电影。 3. Suddenly it all falls out of relation to her basic henny self, and she realizes she has lost her life. 瞬间这一切与她如母鸡一样的本性毫无关系，她意识到她已失去了自己的生活。 4. Knowledge of self increases as one gets older. 随着年岁的增长，人们的自我认识也不断加深。 5. I was looking for some resemblance between my ancestor and my self. 我在寻找我的祖先和我自己之间的某些相似之处。', '名词复数: selves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('influential', '[ˌɪnflu\'enʃl]', 'adj.有权势的；有影响的 n.有影响力的人物', '1. He used his influential friends to help him get into the civil service by the back door. 他利用那些有权有势的朋友帮助他走后门,到政府行政部门任职。 2. You may be fated to have a very influential incarnation. 你可能注定是一种非常有权势的化身。 3. Influential friends helped him to get a good job. 有权势的朋友们帮他弄到一份美差。 4. She uses her influential friends to get jobs. 她利用有势力的朋友找到工作。 5. He met a select group of media influentials. 他会见了一群经过挑选的媒介巨头。', '副词: influentially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('myth', '[mɪθ]', 'n.神话；虚构的故事', '1. This is the story of a myth of our times. 这是一个关于我们这个时代的神话故事。 2. Venus is one of the goddess in Greek myth. 维纳斯是希腊神话中的女神之一。 3. The rich uncle of whom he boasts is only a myth. 他吹嘘的那个有钱的叔叔只是个乌有翁。 4. His story about is very wealthy is a complete myth. 关于他非常富有的说法完全是捏造出来的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bacon', '[\'beɪkən]', 'n.培根；咸肉；熏肉', '1. I\'ll plump for bacon and eggs rather than breakfast cereal. 我宁愿吃咸肉和鸡蛋，而不愿吃谷类制作的早餐食品。 2. The bacon is all frizzled up! 腌肉都煎糊了！ 3. I\'ll rustle up some eggs and bacon for you. 我给你弄些鸡蛋和腌猪肉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cage', '[keɪdʒ]', 'n.笼子；监狱；笼状结构 vt.关入笼中', '1. The old man wants to buy a cage for birds. 老人想买一个鸟笼。 2. Is it cruel to confine a bird in a cage? 把鸟关在笼子里残忍不残忍? 3. The hamster had got through the wire at the front of its cage. 仓鼠从其笼子前部的栅栏处钻出去了。 4. The canary was trilling away in its cage. 那只金丝雀在笼中鸣啾。 5. You can cage a bird, but you cannot make him sing. 你可以关住一只鸟，但你不能使它唱歌。', '过去式: caged 过去分词: caged 现在分词: caging 第三人称单数: cages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sow', '[saʊ]', 'v.播种；散布 n.母猪', '1. These seeds should be sown in April. 这些种子应在四月播种。 2. His words had sowed the seeds of suspicion in their minds. 他的话已在他们心中播下怀疑的种子。 3. The enemy tried to sow discontent among our men . 敌人企图在我们的士兵中间散布不满情绪。', '名词: sower 过去式: sowed 过去分词: sown/sowed 现在分词: sowing 第三人称单数: sows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('boss', '[bɔːs]', 'n.老板；上司；首脑 v.管理；指挥', '1. My boss is a football fan. 我的上司是一位足球迷。 2. He was fired by his boss. 他被他的老板解雇了。 3. He is my sometime boss. 他是我从前的上司。 4. Bob liked to boss the young man about. 鲍伯喜爱对那位年轻人发号施令。', '过去式: bossed 过去分词: bossed 现在分词: bossing 第三人称单数: bosses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lofty', '[\'lɔːfti]', 'adj.高的；崇高的；高尚的；傲慢的', '1. There are lofty fells behind this village. 这个村庄后面是高高的荒山。 2. Longer shadow falls from lofty mountain. 山高投影长。 3. They saw the lofty peak in all its majesty. 他们看到了高耸的山峰，气势雄伟壮丽。 4. He has lent his name to the lofty cause. 他以自己的名义支持这一崇高的事业。', '副词: loftily 比较级: loftier 最高级: loftiest 名词: loftiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accidental', '[ˌæksɪ\'dentl]', 'adj. 意外的； 偶然的； 附属的 n. 偶然； 不重要的东西； <音>变调的临时符号', '1. Banging may also be accidental and painful. 这种撞击也可以是意外的及产生痛苦的。 2. He discovered an accidental error in his composition. 他在作文里发现了一个意外的错误。 3. Their marriage was quite accidental. 他们的结合是偶然的。 4. Your sin\'s not accidental, but a trade. 你的犯罪不是偶然的过失，你已经把它当作一件不足为奇的常事。 5. Their marriage was quite accidental. 他们的结合是偶然的。', '副词: accidentally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('normalization', '[ˌnɔːməlaɪ\'zeɪʃn]', 'n.常态化；正常化；正规化', '1. Normalization of Sino-U.S. relations was thus achieved. 自此，中美关系实现正常化。 2. Measures are being taken to promote the normalization of relation between the two countries. 他们正采取措施以促进两国关系的正常化。 3. Management enters the safe management system of normalization. 管理进入正规化的安全管理系统。 4. Experts believe the regular flights symbolize the normalization in air transport across the strait. 专家称这次定期航班的施行象征着海峡两岸航空运输的正规化。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('curb', '[kɜːrb]', 'n.路边；克制；勒马绳 vt.抑制；勒住；牵(狗)到合适地方大小便', '1. He parked his car along the curb. 他把汽车停靠在路边。 2. I stood at the curb trying to breathe. 我站在人行道沿上想缓口气。 3. You must try to put a curb on your bad temper. 你必须学着克制自己暴躁的脾气。 4. High interest rates put a curb on spending. 高利率抑制了消费 5. I could be able to curb my desires. 我能够抑制住自己的欲望。', '过去式: curbed 过去分词: curbed 现在分词: curbing 第三人称单数: curbs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('honest', '[\'ɑːnɪst]', 'adj.诚实的；正直的；坦率的', '1. Her action declared her to be an honest woman. 她的行为足以说明她是一个诚实的女人。 2. It was commonly believed that he was an honest man. 一般都认为他是一个诚实的人。 3. The article is an attempt to defame an honest man. 这篇文章旨在诋毁一个正直的人。 4. An honest judge cannot be servile to public opinion. 一个正直的法官不能一味顺从舆论。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('personality', '[ˌpɜːrsə\'næləti]', 'n.个性；名人；特色', '1. His personality comes through in his writing. 他的个性体现在他的文章中。 2. She has a very strong personality. 她个性很强。 3. He is one of the best-known personalities in the world of tennis. 他是网球界最著名的人物之一。 4. His wife was very beautiful, but seemed to have no personality. 他的妻子很漂亮,但似乎没有什么特点。', '名词复数: personalities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('how', '[haʊ]', 'adv.怎样；多么；如何 conj.如何；怎样；以 ... 方式 n.方式', '1. How can we divert her thoughts from her sad loss? 我们怎样才能使他不再想到她可悲的损失？ 2. How can I drive away these feelings of sadness? 我该怎样做才能驱散忧伤？ 3. How pleasant it is to dine on Chinese food! 吃上中餐是多么令人愉快啊！ 4. How grand the mountains look in the early evening! 暮色中群山是多么壮丽！ 5. It was difficult to gauge how people would respond. 大家的反应如何难以估计。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lunch', '[lʌntʃ]', 'n.午餐 v.吃(午餐)；提供(午餐)', '1. We had a wonderful lunch. 我们吃了顿很不错的午餐。 2. Let\'s get together for lunch. 让我们一起吃顿午餐吧。 3. I can lunch off the bread left over from yesterday. 午餐我可以吃昨天剩下的面包。 4. We shall be delighted if you\'ll lunch with us. 你要能来和我们一道吃午饭，我们就高兴了。', '名词: luncher 过去式: lunched 过去分词: lunched 现在分词: lunching 第三人称单数: lunches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('collective', '[kə\'lektɪv]', 'adj.集体的；共同的 n.集体', '1. Chorus is a collective vocality performing art. 合唱是集体的声乐表演艺术。 2. Have you any excuse to offer for frequent absence from collective practice? 你经常不参加集体训练有什么解释吗？ 3. They hold together for collective security. 他们为了共同安全而团结在一起。 4. We all bear collective responsibility for this decision. 我们大家共同承担这项决定的责任。 5. I also learned the strength of the collective. 我还认识到了集体的力量。', '副词: collectively 名词: collectiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jacket', '[\'dʒækɪt]', 'n.短上衣；茄克衫；皮；护封；绝缘护套 vt.加外套；装封套', '1. He wore a pair of dark glasses and a jacket all day long. 他整天戴一副墨眼镜，穿一件短上衣。 2. My jacket is made of otter skins. 我的皮夹克是用水獭皮做的。 3. She wore a leather jacket studded with rhinestones. 她穿了一件镶有人造钻石的皮外套。 4. Jacket potatoes, ie potatoes baked without being peeled. 带皮烤熟的土豆。', '形容词: jacketed 过去式: jacketed 过去分词: jacketed 现在分词: jacketing 第三人称单数: jackets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('community', '[kə\'mjuːnəti]', 'n.社区；社会；公众；共同体；团体；共享；共有；[生]群落', '1. Here is a local Jewish community. 这是当地犹太人的一个社区。 2. Everyone should invest some time in community service. 每个人都应该花些时间在社区服务上。 3. Community colleges have become popular and their enrollments have increased rapidly. 社区大学日渐增多，报名人数迅速增长。 4. The international community forbids use of any chemical weapons. 国际社会禁止使用一切化学武器。', '名词复数: communities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('together', '[tə\'ɡeðər]', 'adv.共同；一起；协调；一致；连续地 adj.有能力的；镇定的', '1. Let\'s join hands and struggle together. 咱们携起手来共同斗争。 2. Let us rejoice together on your success. 让我们共同庆祝你的成功。 3. They lived together as husband and wife for years. 他们结为夫妇共同生活了很多年。 4. They traveled together. 他们一起旅游。 5. He\'s incredibly together for someone so young. 他这个人年纪轻轻，办事如此稳当，真是了不起。', '名词: togetherness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ladder', '[\'lædər]', 'n.阶梯；梯子；梯状物', '1. Diligence is often a ladder to success. 勤勉常常是通往成功的阶梯。 2. He was halfway down the ladder when he fell. 他下阶梯时，半路摔倒了。 3. This ladder isn\'t very stable. 这架梯子不太牢靠。 4. It\'s considered unlucky to walk under a ladder. 从梯子下面走过被认为是不吉利的。', '过去式: laddered 过去分词: laddered 现在分词: laddering 第三人称单数: ladders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('streamline', '[\'striːmlaɪn]', 'v.使 ... 成流线型；使 ... 合理化；使简化', '1. I know you can streamline this kind of airship. 我知道你能把这种飞艇设计成流线型。 2. The V-shaped nose guard helps to streamline the design. 这款V字型的护鼻塞有助于它的流线型设计。 3. The aim is to streamline the business and achieve higher productivity. 目标是将业务合理化，提高生产力。 4. He endeavored to streamline the plant organization. 他努力使工厂组织简化而更有效地运作。', '过去式: streamlined 过去分词: streamlined 现在分词: streamlining 第三人称单数: streamlines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('list', '[lɪst]', 'n.目录；名单；明细表；条纹；倾斜；<古>意向 v.列出；(使)倾斜；<古>使高兴；愿意；<古>听', '1. We should get the samples on the list to check. 我们应该索取目录上的样品来检验一下。 2. She complained about the omission of her name from the list. 她抱怨名单上遗漏了她的名字。 3. He wrote down his name on the list. 他将他的名字写在清单上。 4. Can you give me a price list with specification? 你能否给我一份有规格说明的价目单吗？ 5. We were asked to list our ten favourite songs. 我们应要求列出自己最喜爱的十首歌曲。', '名词: lister 过去式: listed 过去分词: listed 现在分词: listing 第三人称单数: lists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shiver', '[\'ʃɪvər]', 'v.颤动；发抖 v.打碎 n.冷颤；哆嗦 n.碎块', '1. She shivered at the thought of going into the dark house alone. 她想到要独自走进那所黑洞洞的房子里去就不寒而粟。 2. The child shivered from the cold. 这孩子冷得发抖。 3. He was beginning to shiver as the intense cold pervaded the room. 整个房间冰冷彻骨,他开始冷得发抖了。 4. He shivered the mirror with a hammer . 他用铁锤打碎镜子。 5. I could not repress a shiver whenever I thought of him. 我一想到他就忍不住颤抖。 6. He cut his foot on a small shiver of glass. 玻璃碎片把他的脚划破了。', '过去式: shivered 过去分词: shivered 现在分词: shivering 第三人称单数: shivers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diversion', '[daɪ\'vɜːrʒn]', 'n.转向；转移；娱乐活动；临时绕行', '1. There\'s a diversion sign behind the lorry. 那辆卡车后面发出了转向的信号。 2. The diversion of a stream changed the land. 一条小溪的转向使这块土地发生了变化。 3. A smoke bomb created a diversion while the robbery took place. 劫案发生时，一枚烟雾弹转移了人们的视线。 4. I think your last argument was a diversion to make us forget the main point. 我认为你最后的那个论点是在转移目标，以便我们忘掉要点。', '形容词: diversionary');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lubricate', '[\'luːbrɪkeɪt]', 'v.润滑；加润滑剂', '1. My throat needs lubricating. 我需要润润嗓子了。 2. We find it necessary to lubricate machines. 我们认为给机器加润滑油是必要的。 3. If you never bother to lubricate your engine, of course it will seize up. 如果你老是怕麻烦，不给发动机添加润滑油，发动机当然会失灵卡住啦。', '形容词: lubricative 名词: lubrication 过去式: lubricated 过去分词: lubricated 现在分词: lubricating 第三人称单数: lubricates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('danger', '[\'deɪndʒər]', 'n.【U】危险 n.【C】危险物（或人）；威胁', '1. She was on the danger list, but is much better now. 她曾一度病危，现在好多了。 2. The operation is a success and now the patient is out of danger. 手术成功了，病人现在已脱离危险。 3. Violent criminals like that are dangers to society. 那种暴力罪犯对社会是一种危害。 4. A gun could be regarded as a danger when it\'s in a criminal\'s hand. 当枪在罪犯手里的时候就成为危险物品了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cell', '[sel]', 'n.单人牢房；小房间；细胞；蜂房的巢室；电池；政治小组；(计算机电子表格的)单元格；<美口>手机', '1. The prisoner was locked in a cell. 那囚犯被关在单人牢房内。 2. She was found prostrate on the floor of the cell. 有人发现她趴在小屋的地板上。 3. The cancer cell may invade other parts of the body. 癌细胞可能侵袭身体的其他部分。 4. There is a queen bee in the cell. 蜂房里有一只蜂王。', '过去式: celled 过去分词: celled 现在分词: celling 第三人称单数: cells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('investment', '[ɪn\'vestmənt]', 'n.投资；投资额；投入', '1. Antiques are a very safe investment. 古玩是一种非常保险的投资对象。 2. The firm has made a huge investment in new plant. 该公司投入巨资购置新设备。 3. Great changes are in prospect in this area due to foreign investment. 因为外资的引进，该地区会发生很大变化。 4. Investment is turning up sharply. 投资额急遽增长。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tight', '[taɪt]', 'adj.紧的；紧身的；密集的；拮据的 adv.紧紧地；牢固地；迅速地', '1. This pair of trousers is too tight for me. 这条裤子我穿太紧了。 2. This drawer is too tight for me to open it. 这抽屉太紧了，我打不开。 3. That fat woman looked ridiculous in her tight golden dress. 那位胖妇人穿着金色的紧身礼服，显得滑稽可笑。 4. Don\'t they know how tight my schedule is? 他们不晓得我的日程安排有多紧吗? 5. She held her baby tight in her arms. 她紧紧地搂着她的孩子。', '副词: tightly 比较级: tighter 最高级: tightest 名词: tightness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hour', '[\'aʊər]', 'n.小时；钟点', '1. It took him half an hour to finish the work. 他花了半个小时做完这项工作。 2. The London bus departs every hour on the hour. 伦敦的公共汽车每小时零分开出一趟。 3. You can hire a bicycle by the hour to go around the city. 你可以按钟点租辆自行车在城里观光。 4. The boy will sit there hour after hour looking at the traffic go by. 那男孩常常坐在那里好几个钟点,看着车辆行人通过。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ignite', '[ɪɡ\'naɪt]', 'vi.着火；燃烧 vt.点燃；使 ... 燃烧；引发', '1. Large pieces of wood do not ignite easily. 大块木材是不易着火的。 2. Ammonia-air mixtures are quite difficult to ignite. 氨与空气的混合气体不易燃烧。 3. The burning gases can ignite the lean mixture. 燃烧着的气体能点燃稀的混合气。 4. What can you do to ignite your own passion? 有什么办法可以点燃你的热情？', '形容词: ignitable 名词: igniter 过去式: ignited 过去分词: ignited 现在分词: igniting 第三人称单数: ignites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wealthy', '[\'welθi]', 'adj.富有的 n.富人', '1. She\'s an attractive woman, and wealthy to boot. 她是个很有魅力的女人，而且很富有。 2. A wealthy sponsor came to our rescue with a generous donation. 有个富有的赞助人慷慨捐赠来解救我们。 3. He was the son of a wealthy planter. 他是一个富有的种植园主的儿子。 4. She married her daughter to a wealthy man. 她把她女儿嫁给了一个富人。', '副词: wealthily 比较级: wealthier 最高级: wealthiest 名词: wealthiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consecutive', '[kən\'sekjətɪv]', 'adj.连续的；连贯的', '1. It has rained for four consecutive days. 已连续下了四天雨。 2. He was re-elected for four consecutive terms. 他连着四届当选。 3. The policy of our Party is consecutive. 我党的政策始终如一。', '副词: consecutively 名词: consecutiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('entire', '[ɪn\'taɪər]', 'adj.全部的；完整的；全面的', '1. I am in entire agreement with you. 我完全同意你。 2. The entire population was wiped out by the terrible disease. 所有的居民都被可怕的疾病夺去了生命。 3. He wrote the entire play in only two weeks. 整个剧本只花了他两个星期时间。 4. The foul odor penetrated the entire house. 难闻的臭气弥漫于整个房间。', '名词: entireness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('theoretical', '[ˌθiːə\'retɪkl]', 'adj.理论上的', '1. These findings have both theoretical and practical applications. 这些发现具有理论和实际的应用。 2. Theoretical study must be closely integrated with practice. 理论学习要紧密结合实际。 3. It\'s a theoretical possibility, but I don\'t suppose it will happen. 这是一种理论上的可能性，但我认为这种情况不会发生。', '副词: theoretically 异体字: theoretic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evident', '[\'evɪdənt]', 'adj.明白的；明显的', '1. Now it became evident that he spoke two languages at once. 现在我才明白，原来他心里一套表面一套。 2. Inertia is evident in our every day experiences. 惯性在我们日常生活中是很常见的。 3. The purpose may not be immediately evident. 这种目的不一定显而易见。 4. The rationale for the present study is evident. 该研究的理论基础是明显的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('distort', '[dɪ\'stɔːrt]', 'vt.歪曲；扭曲；变形 vi.歪曲', '1. The reporter distorted the facts. 记者们歪曲了事实。 2. How dare he distort the facts so brazenly! 他怎么敢如此肆无忌惮地歪曲事实！ 3. The government was accused of having systematically distorted the protester\'s case. 政府因为有计划地歪曲抗议者的观点而受到责难。 4. This journalist distorted the spokesman\'s remarks. 这名记者曲解了该发言人的话。 5. The bias of a reporter can easily distort the news. 记者的偏见很容易歪曲新闻的报导。', '名词: distorter 过去式: distorted 过去分词: distorted 现在分词: distorting 第三人称单数: distorts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inferior', '[ɪn\'fɪriər]', 'adj.较低的；次等的；不如的；下级的 n.下级；属下；[印]下标符号', '1. These people occupy an inferior position in local society. 这些人在当地社会居于下等地位。 2. Captain is an inferior rank to major. 上尉是低于少校的一个官阶 3. A cheaper camera is not always inferior to a more expensive one. 廉价照相机的质量并总不比昂贵的差。 4. They never sell inferior goods. 他们从不销售次货。 5. A gentleman should always be civil, even to his inferiors. 有教养的人应该一直很有礼貌，甚至对待下属也一样。', '名词: inferiority');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('multitude', '[\'mʌltɪtuːd]', 'n.大量；多数；群众', '1. A multitude of heroic figures emerge. 大量英雄人物出现了。 2. An angry multitude collected in the street. 街道上聚集了一大群愤怒的人。 3. There are a multitude of reasons against it. 有许多反对理由。 4. The multitude may laugh at his music, but we know better. 一般人也许会嘲笑他的音乐，但我们更了解它。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adverse', '[\'ædvɜːrs]', 'adj.不利的；逆向的；有害的', '1. The judge gave us an adverse decision. 法官作出对我们不利的判决。 2. He ignored all kinds of adverse comments about him. 他不理睬各种各样对他不利的评论。 3. The development was adverse to our interests. 这种发展与我们的利益背道而驰。 4. Diseases are adverse to the best growth of children. 疾病对儿童的健康成长是有害的。', '副词: adversely 名词: adverseness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('excessive', '[ɪk\'sesɪv]', 'adj.过分的；过多的', '1. Excessive patriotism can lead to xenophobia. 爱国主义过了头即可导致仇视一切外国人。 2. Excessive dosage of this drug can result in injury to the liver. 这种药使用过量会损害肝脏。 3. The quality of urban living has been damaged by excessive noise levels. 城市生活的质量已被过度的噪音所破坏。 4. I consider the excessive smoking and drinking tend to cloud the brain. 我认为过多的抽烟和过量的酗酒，会使人的头脑迟钝。', '副词: excessively 名词: excessiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('global', '[\'ɡloʊbl]', 'adj.全球性的；总的；球状的', '1. The green campaign is a global phenomenon. 绿色运动是全球性的现象。 2. Air pollution is a global problem. 空气污染是全球性的问题。 3. The shortage of water has become a global problem. 水能短缺已经是全球性的问题了。 4. We have the responsibility to keep the global strategic balance and stability. 我们有义务维持全球战略的平衡肯稳定。', '副词: globally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('staff', '[stæf]', 'n.员工；全体人员；全体职员；拐杖；杆；棒；五线谱 vt.配备员工', '1. I find the hotel staff particularly courteous. 我发现饭店员工特别谦恭有礼。', '名词复数: staffs 过去式: staffed 过去分词: staffed 现在分词: staffing 第三人称单数: staffs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intention', '[ɪn\'tenʃn]', 'n.意图；目的；意向；打算', '1. I held back not knowing his real intention. 我有点犹豫不定,不知道他的真正意图是什么。 2. What do you think was the author\'s intention in this passage? 你认为作者写这一段的用意是什麽? 3. Acquaint him with your intention. 让他知道你的意向。 4. Have you heard of her intention to resign? 你听到她打算辞职的传闻了吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('friction', '[\'frɪkʃn]', 'n.摩擦；摩擦力；分歧', '1. Constant friction wore out the heels of my shoes. 不断的摩擦磨损了我的鞋跟。 2. Matches are lighted by friction. 火柴由摩擦而生火。 3. Friction lowers the efficiency of a machine. 摩擦减低机器的效率。 4. Friction causes a rolling ball to stop finally. 摩擦力使滚动的球最终停了下来。', '形容词: frictional 副词: frictionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disregard', '[ˌdɪsrɪ\'ɡɑːrd]', 'vt.不顾；忽视 n.漠视；不理会', '1. We cannot disregard his coming late to work so often. 对他上班经常迟到,我们不能不管。 2. He doesn\'t disregard the footnotes. 他并没有不注意脚注。 3. He disregarded his doctor\'s advice. 他无视医生的劝告。 4. You can\'t just disregard the security problem. 你可不能忽视安全问题。 5. The official has shown a total disregard for the needs of the poor. 这个官员对穷人的需求表现出完全漠视的态度。', '形容词: disregardful 名词: disregarder 过去式: disregarded 过去分词: disregarded 现在分词: disregarding 第三人称单数: disregards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('classmate', '[\'klæsmeɪt]', 'n.同班同学', '1. He is my classmate of junior middle school. 他是我初中时的同班同学。 2. He helped a classmate who was behind with his homework. 他帮助一位没有按时完成作业的同班同学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hesitate', '[\'hezɪteɪt]', 'vi.犹豫；不情愿；口吃', '1. Do not hesitate to tell us if you have a problem . 你有问题就直截了当地告诉我们。 2. I would hesitate to get involved in this adventure. 我犹豫是否参加这次探险。 3. She hesitated to hurt the child\'s feelings. 她不想伤害孩子的感情。 4. I hesitate to spend so much money on clothes. 我舍不得把这麽多钱花在穿衣服上.', '副词: hesitatingly 名词: hesitation 过去式: hesitated 过去分词: hesitated 现在分词: hesitating 第三人称单数: hesitates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commemorate', '[kə\'meməreɪt]', 'vt.纪念', '1. A monument was built to commemorate the victory. 为了纪念胜利，建造了一座纪念碑。 2. Christmas commemorates the birth of Christ. 圣诞节是为了纪念耶酥的诞生。 3. They reared a monument to commemorate the great musician. 他们建立起一座纪念碑，纪念这位伟大的音乐家。 4. We celebrate this day to commemorate the brave soldiers. 我们庆祝这天，以纪念英勇的士兵。', '名词: commemorator 过去式: commemorated 过去分词: commemorated 现在分词: commemorating 第三人称单数: commemorates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('desirable', '[dɪ\'zaɪərəbl]', 'adj.令人满意的；性感的；有吸引力的；值得的；令人向往的 n.有吸引力的人或物', '1. It is desirable that we (should) provide for the poor at Christmas. 在圣诞节施舍穷人是可喜的事。 2. It is desirable that atomic energy should be used for peaceful purpose. 原子能应该为了和平的目的而使用，这是合乎情理的。 3. You will also make some desirable acquaintances. 你也可以结识几个合意的朋友。 4. He found her intensely desirable. 他觉得她极其性感。 5. The girl is a desirable. 这个女孩是个有吸引力的人。', '副词: desirably 名词: desirability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('catastrophe', '[kə\'tæstrəfi]', 'n.大灾难；大祸；彻底失败', '1. The earthquake was a terrible catastrophe. 这次地震是个可怕的灾难。 2. He is teetering on the edge of catastrophe. 他在大灾难的边缘徘徊。 3. The catastrophe would be stamped in their minds. 那场灾难将会深深地印在他们的头脑里。 4. Their other problems paled into insignificance beside this latest catastrophe. 最近发生这一灾祸后,他们其他的问题都显得无关重要了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('convenient', '[kən\'viːnjənt]', 'adj.便利的；方便的', '1. Internet makes it convenient for us to get in touch with each other. 互联网使得我们相互联系便利了。 2. Please come whenever it is convenient to you. 方便的时候,请随时来。', '副词: conveniently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crazy', '[\'kreɪzi]', 'adj.疯狂的；荒唐的；着迷的 n.荒唐的人 adv.疯狂地', '1. Are you crazy? 你疯了吗？ 2. It drives me crazy. 它使我快要发疯了。 3. The mother of the kidnapped child was crazy with worry. 那个被绑架的孩子的母亲担心得几乎发狂了。 4. What started him off on this crazy idea? 他这个荒唐的主意是哪儿来的?', '副词: crazily 比较级: crazier 最高级: craziest 名词: craziness 名词复数: crazies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('have', '[həv]', 'aux.已经 vt.有；吃；得到；从事；允许；雇用；享有 n.[常用复数]富人，有产者，有钱人；富国', '1. A country must have the will to repel any invader. 一个国家得有决心击退任何入侵者。 2. The police have absolute proof of his guilt. 警方有他犯罪的确凿证据。 3. Have a glass of beer to rinse your dinner down. 喝杯啤酒把你吃的晚饭冲下去。 4. We will have pork chops for dinner. 我们晚餐吃猪排。', '过去式: had 过去分词: had 现在分词: having 第三人称单数: has');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intellectual', '[ˌɪntə\'lektʃuəl]', 'n.凭理智做事者；知识分子 adj.智力的；聪明的', '1. He likes to set himself up as an intellectual. 他喜欢自命为知识分子。 2. These views were common among intellectuals. 这些观点在知识分子中很普遍。 3. The argument was too intellectual for me; I couldn\'t follow a word of it. 这场争论对我来说太深奥了，我一点都搞不明白。 4. Chess is a highly intellectual game. 象棋是需用高度智力的运动项目。', '副词: intellectually 名词: intellectuality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feast', '[fiːst]', 'n.宴会；酒席；节会 v.享乐；款宴；请客', '1. The king held a feast for us. 国王为我们举行了盛大的宴会。 2. Enough is as good as a feast. 知足常乐。 3. Preparing for the Christmas Eve feast makes me at my wit\'s end. 筹办圣诞宴会简直使我智穷才竭。 4. His friend treats him to a sumptuous feast. 朋友摆上了丰盛的酒席。 5. He feasted his eye on the beautiful scene. 他尽情欣赏这美丽的景色。', '名词: feaster 过去式: feasted 过去分词: feasted 现在分词: feasting 第三人称单数: feasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('singular', '[\'sɪŋɡjələr]', 'adj.单数的；奇特的；非凡的 n.单数', '1. \"It\" is the third-person singular neuter pronoun. “it”是第三人称单数的中性代名词。 2. I was struck with the man\'s singular appearance. 那个人的奇特外貌给我留下了深刻的印象。 3. Talking to him is a singular experience. 与他交谈是一种非同平常的体验。 4. She had a singular insight into life. 她对于人生有一个非凡的了解。 5. Give the singular forms of the following nouns. 写出下列名词的单数形式。', '副词: singularly 名词: singularness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('china', '[\'tʃaɪnə]', 'n.中国 n.[小写]瓷器', '1. Beijing is the capital of China. 北京是中国的首都。 2. China does a lot of trade with many countries. 中国和许多国家进行多方面贸易。 3. China is an oriental country with a long history. 中国是一个有着悠久历史的东方国家。 4. All our glass and china is kept in the cupboard. 我们所有的玻璃和陶瓷器皿都放在柜橱里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blade', '[bleɪd]', 'n.刀刃；刀锋；桨叶；叶片', '1. The blade needs sharpening. 这刀刃需要磨一磨。 2. The blade slashed his leg open. 刀刃把他的腿划破了。 3. The blade is chipped in a few places. 刀锋有几个地方缺口。 4. The propellar blade is powered by a diesel engine. 螺旋桨叶由柴油发动机驱动。', '形容词: bladed');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whirl', '[wɜːrl]', 'v.使 ... 旋转；回旋；迅速移动；头晕目眩 n.回旋；旋转；一个接一个的活动；混乱；尝试', '1. It may whirl either clockwise or counterclockwise. 它可能顺时针方向或反时针方向旋转。 2. The electron continues to whirl about the proton. 电子继续绕着质子转。 3. The wind whirled the dead leaves about. 风吹得枯叶在四处回旋。 4. The houses whirled past us as the train gathered speed. 火车越开越快，周围的房子在我们旁边一闪而过。 5. The colorful whirl of the dancer is beautiful to watch. 舞蹈者多彩多姿的旋转令人赏心悦目。', '名词: whirler 过去式: whirled 过去分词: whirled 现在分词: whirling 第三人称单数: whirls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arch', '[ɑːrtʃ]', 'n.拱；拱门；拱状物 v.成拱形；拱起 adj.主要的；调皮的', '1. Dip your head under the low arch. 在低矮的门拱下要低头。 2. A pointed arch drawn from two centers within the span. 在跨度内有两个中心点，连接两个中心点的是弧度突出的拱。 3. Have you been to the Triumphal Arch? 你去过凯旋门吗？ 4. The bridge has three arches. 这座桥有三座拱洞。 5. The cat arched its back when it saw the dog. 那猫看见狗时就拱起了背。 6. They considered him their arch opponent. 他们将他看成是主要对手。', '副词: archly 名词: archness 过去式: arched 过去分词: arched 现在分词: arching 第三人称单数: arches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('miracle', '[\'mɪrəkl]', 'n.奇迹', '1. Her life was saved by a miracle. 她的生命是靠奇迹救活的。 2. The compact disc is a miracle of modern technology. 激光唱片是当代技术的奇葩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skirt', '[skɜːrt]', 'n.裙子；下摆；边缘；郊区；挡板 v.装边于；位于(边缘)；绕开', '1. How many skirts do you have? 你有多少条裙子？ 2. She tore her skirt on the nail. 钉子勾破了她的裙子。 3. Her skirt has very exquisite lace. 她的裙子有非常精致的花边。 4. She smoothed down the skirt of her dress. 她把连衣裙的下摆弄平。 5. The road skirted the woods. 这条路环绕林子。', '过去式: skirted 过去分词: skirted 现在分词: skirting 第三人称单数: skirts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('several', '[\'sevrəl]', 'pron.若干 adj.几个的；若干的；各自的', '1. I bought several books yesterday. 我昨天买了好几本书。 2. My husband has several shirts of different colors. 我丈夫有好几件颜色不同的衬衫。 3. The regime has been propped up by several monopoly capitalists. 那个政权一直是受到若干垄断资本家的支持而维持着的。 4. They shook hands and went their several ways. 他们握了手,然后各自走各的路。', '副词: severally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('merge', '[mɜːrdʒ]', 'v.合并；融合；兼并', '1. His department will merge with mine. 他的部门将和我的合并。 2. The two marching columns moved closer and finally merged. 行进中的两路纵队越走越近，终于合成一路。 3. The shadows slowly merge together. 这些阴影慢慢地融合在一起了。 4. The water and the sky merge into a pure whole. 水与天连成一线,不染纤尘。', '名词: mergence 过去式: merged 过去分词: merged 现在分词: merging 第三人称单数: merges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('truck', '[trʌk]', 'n.卡车；手推车；敞篷货车 n.交易；交往；商品蔬菜；实物工资；<口>垃圾 v.以卡车运 v.交易；打交道', '1. The truck was heavily loaded. 这辆卡车装载很重。 2. They transported the goods by truck. 他们用卡车运货。 3. Move cylinders using a suitable hand truck or cart. 用合适的手推车或移动钢瓶。 4. Shortly, he bought a cart, then a truck, and then he had his own fleet of delivery vehicles. 很短的时间里，他买了个手推车，然后卡车，接着他有了自己的运输车队。 5. We\'ll have no further truck with them. 我们将不再同他们做生意。 6. They trucked the goods over immediately. 他们用卡车立刻把这批货物运送过去。', '过去式: trucked 过去分词: trucked 现在分词: trucking 第三人称单数: trucks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poisonous', '[\'pɔɪzənəs]', 'adj.有毒的；恶意的', '1. Some mushrooms are poisonous. 有些蘑菇有毒。 2. Some snakes have poisonous fangs. 有些蛇长有毒牙。 3. She gave him a poisonous look. 她恶狠狠地瞪了他一眼。 4. He said some poisonous things to me. 他对我说了一些恶毒的事。', '副词: poisonously 名词: poisonousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diverse', '[daɪ\'vɜːrs]', 'adj.不同的；多种多样的', '1. They are the people from diverse cultures. 他们是些有着不同文化背景的人。 2. Since then，she has played a diverse range of roles. 从那时起,她出演了各种不同的角色。 3. Her interests are very diverse. 她的兴趣非常广泛。 4. Their way of life is rich, diverse and rooted. 他们的生活方式丰富多彩,多种多样,扎根传统。', '副词: diversely 名词: diverseness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('saint', '[seɪnt]', 'n.圣人；圣徒 vt.把 ... 封为圣人', '1. They named their child after the saint. 他们用圣人的名字来给他们的孩子命名. 2. Only a saint can put up with her children. 只有圣人才能容忍她的孩子们。 3. After he died, the Church declared him a saint. 在他去世之后，他生前所在的教堂宣布他为圣徒。 4. Nature to a saint is sacramental. 对一个圣徒来说，自然是神圣的。 5. Confucian doctrine exerted a profound influence on later ages, so Confucius is addressed respectfully as a saint. 孔子的儒家学说对后世影响深远，因而他被世人尊为圣人。', '过去式: sainted 过去分词: sainted 现在分词: sainting 第三人称单数: saints');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('typewriter', '[\'taɪpraɪtər]', 'n.打字机', '1. The computer is more expensive than the typewriter. 这部电脑比这部打字机更贵。 2. The typewriter is at your service. 这台打字机随便你使用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('uncover', '[ʌn\'kʌvər]', 'vt.揭开；揭露', '1. Geologists uncover hidden riches. 地质学家揭开隐埋的宝藏。 2. And the one person who can help him uncover the truth is not a cop at all. 可帮他揭开真相的人却根本不是警察。 3. Be discreet about any information you uncover. 揭露任何信息都要谨慎。 4. Overcome the odds to uncover the conspiracy and clear your name. 克服困难，以揭露这一阴谋，并明确您的姓名。', '过去式: uncovered 过去分词: uncovered 现在分词: uncovering 第三人称单数: uncovers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('freedom', '[\'friːdəm]', 'n.自由；直率；特许，特权', '1. Democracy is a bulwark of freedom. 民主是自由的保障。 2. They bought peace with their freedom. 他们牺牲自由换取和平。 3. By persistence many countries won freedom. 通过坚持不懈的努力, 许多国家赢得了自由。 4. Slavery is the antithesis of freedom. 奴役与自由是对立的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('notorious', '[noʊ\'tɔːriəs]', 'adj.臭名昭著的', '1. He is notorious for his goings-on. 他因行为不检点而声名狼藉。 2. The district is notorious for its fogs. 那地区以浓雾出名。 3. Hitler is a notorious dictator. 希特勒是一个臭名昭著的独裁者。 4. The notorious thief will be put up for trial next week. 那个臭名昭著的偷窃犯将于下周出庭受审。', '副词: notoriously 名词: notoriousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('confuse', '[kən\'fjuːz]', 'vt.使困惑；使混乱；混淆', '1. They asked so many questions that they confused me. 他们问了许许多多问题，把我弄糊涂了。 2. Your explanation does not so much enlighten us as confuse us. 你的解释没有起到启发作用,反而把我们弄糊涂了。 3. Her unexpected arrival confused all our plans. 她突然来到把我们所有的计划全打乱了. 4. Please don\'t confuse Australia with Austria. 别把澳大利亚和奥地利混淆了。', '副词: confusingly 过去式: confused 过去分词: confused 现在分词: confusing 第三人称单数: confuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('side', '[saɪd]', 'n.边；侧；边缘；侧面；(多边形的)边；(立体的)面；一方；方面；旁边；家族 adj.旁的；次要的 v.站在…的一边；支持', '1. My house is the ninth on the right side. 我的房子是右边第九幢。 2. The park is just on the left side of this street. 公园就在马路的左侧。 3. We planted tulips along the side of the lawn. 我们沿草坪的边缘种上了郁金香 4. The town sprawled along the side of the lake. 小镇顺着湖的边缘扩展。 5. He came in through a side door to avoid the crowds. 为了避开人群他从旁边的门进来。 6. She always sided with my brother. 她总是带在我哥哥那边。', '过去式: sided 过去分词: sided 现在分词: siding 第三人称单数: sides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forgive', '[fər\'ɡɪv]', 'v.原谅；宽恕；饶恕', '1. Forgive me. 请原谅我。 2. If he is really repentant, we should forgive him. 如果他真心悔过，我们就应该原谅他。 3. He is not a man who forgives easily. 他不是一个肯轻易宽恕人的人。 4. They forgive the people who trespass against them. 他们总是宽恕冒犯他们的人。', '形容词: forgivable 副词: forgivably 名词: forgiver 过去式: forgave 过去分词: forgiven 现在分词: forgiving 第三人称单数: forgives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('temptation', '[temp\'teɪʃn]', 'n.诱惑；引诱物', '1. I can\'t resist the temptation. 我不能抵挡诱惑。 2. She yielded to temptation and had another chocolate. 她禁不住诱惑，又吃了一块巧克力。 3. She fell an easy victim to his temptation. 她经不起他的诱惑，轻易地被骗了。 4. An expensive bicycle is a temptation to thieves. 高档自行车对窃贼是个诱惑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beyond', '[bɪ\'jɑːnd]', 'prep.超出；远于；除 ... 之外；超出…之外 adv.在更远处；另外 n.远处；来世', '1. The level of inflation has gone beyond 8%. 通货膨胀率已经超过了8%。 2. Such philosophical subtleties are beyond my reach. 这种深奥的哲理我可无法理解。 3. The scenery there was beautiful beyond expression. 那儿的风景美丽得无法形容。 4. The road continues beyond the village up into the hills. 这条路绵延不断越过村子直入山中。 5. They crossed the mountains and travelled to the valleys beyond. 他们越过群山，到了那边的山谷。 6. In future, men can travel to the moon and beyond. 未来人们能到月球或更远处去旅行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('healthy', '[\'helθi]', 'adj.健康的', '1. Although my uncle is old, he looks very strong and healthy. 我的叔叔虽然老了，但他看上去还是很健壮。 2. A healthy shoot should form a strong graft. 健康的嫩枝可以长成强壮的接穗。 3. His inmost thoughts are not healthy. 他心灵深处的思想是不健康的。', '副词: healthily 比较级: healthier 最高级: healthiest 名词: healthiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('branch', '[bræntʃ]', 'n.分部；部门；分店；分支；树枝 v.分岔；分支', '1. Can we drop the car off at any of your branch? 我们可以在你们的任何一家分公司还车吗？ 2. Mr. Smith works in an executive branch of the government. 史密斯先生在政府的行政部门工作。 3. Send these orders down to our branch office. 把这些订货单发送到我们的分店。 4. Gynaecology is a branch of medicine. 妇科学是医学的一个分科。 5. Follow the main road until it branches, and then turn to the right. 顺着这条大路走，在路的分岔口向右拐。', '形容词: branchless 过去式: branched 过去分词: branched 现在分词: branching 第三人称单数: branches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ruby', '[\'ruːbi]', 'adj.红宝石色的 n.红宝石；红宝石色 Ruby：露比（人名）.', '1. The one in Aryan was a soft ruby red. 雅利安的穹顶是一种柔和的红宝石色。 2. Deep Ruby red colour, Morello cherry, raspberry, redcurrant and spices smell. 深红宝石色，有樱桃，红浆果，悬钩子和香料以的味道。 3. Her ruby necklace brightened her face. 红宝石项链照亮了她的脸庞。 4. The genie gave her a big, shiny ruby. 精灵给她一颗又大又闪亮的红宝石。', '名词复数: rubies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('electron', '[ɪ\'lektrɑːn]', 'n.电子', '1. Let us return to electron waves now. 现在我们再回到电子波上来。 2. An electron from one of the atom shells is ejected. 电子从原子的某一壳层中被弹射出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recognition', '[ˌrekəɡ\'nɪʃn]', 'n.承认；认出；赏识', '1. Not until 1916 did the UMW finally win recognition from the anthracite operators 直到1916年，美国矿工联合会才终于得到无烟煤矿资方承认。 2. Not only are we at the forefront of electronics, but we\'ve received worldwide recognition for our advances in chemicals and engineering as well. 我们不仅处于电子技术的前沿,而且我们因在化工和工程领域的进展也得到世界范围的承认。 3. After 25 years the town centre had changed beyond all recognition. 25年过去了,市中心变得认不出来了。 4. My recognition of the face was immediate. 我一下子就认出那张面孔了。', '形容词: recognitory');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('instinct', '[\'ɪnstɪŋkt]', 'n.直觉；本能；天性 adj.充满的', '1. Don\'t trust anything except your instinct. 只管相信你的直觉。 2. She had, too, a true instinct as to the man. 她对这男人还有一种正确的直觉。 3. It is his instinct to reckon on women as constant by their nature. 他的直觉使他认为女人在本质上就是一成不变的。 4. You should not go by instinct in deciding a question. 在决定一个问题时，你不能靠直觉。 5. She likes to hear words instinct with love. 她喜欢听充满爱意的言辞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inform', '[ɪn\'fɔːrm]', 'v.通知；告诉；使熟悉；告发；赋特征于', '1. If you see something suspicious, inform the police at once. 你要是看到什么可疑的东西就马上通知警察。 2. I wasn\'t informed of the decision until it was too late. 等到我得知这项决定时,已经太迟了。 3. The UN Associations work to inform the public about the role the UN plays in global affairs. 联合国协会致力于使公众了解联合国在全球事务中发挥的作用。 4. The defendant informed against the other members of the ring. 被告检举犯罪集团的其他成员。', '过去式: informed 过去分词: informed 现在分词: informing 第三人称单数: informs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('taxi', '[\'tæksi]', 'n.出租车 v.用出租车运送；乘计程车；（飞机）滑行', '1. Let me go shares with you in the taxi fare. 我和你分摊计程车费吧。 2. If you want to ensure that you catch the plane, take a taxi. 你要想确保能赶上那班飞机，就坐出租车去吧。 3. That may be our taxi now! 那辆可能就是我们的计程车了。 4. I got in a taxi and rushed to the company. 我搭了一辆计程车赶往公司。 5. Please taxi documents to the law office. 请用出租汽车把文件送到律师事务所。', '名词复数: taxis 过去式: taxied 过去分词: taxied 现在分词: taxiing/taxying 第三人称单数: taxies/taxis');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('river', '[\'rɪvər]', 'n.河；江；河流；水道', '1. The guide led us to the river. 向导带领我们到河边。 2. Growing along the river are tall palm trees. 沿着这条河生长的是高大的棕树。 3. Navigation is difficult on this river because of the hidden rocks. 因为河上有暗礁，所以在这条河上航行很困难。 4. The bridge stands majestic astride the river. 大桥巍然横跨在江上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pint', '[paɪnt]', 'n.品脱（容量单位，主要在英国、美国及爱尔兰使用）', '1. Draw off another pint of beer, please. 请再量出一品脱啤酒。 2. I bought a pint of milk in the store. 我在这家商店里买了一品脱牛奶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trust', '[trʌst]', 'n.信任；信托 vi.信任 vt.相信；委托', '1. A good marriage is based on trust. 美满的婚姻是建立在互相信任的基础上的。 2. In his will he created trusts for his children. 他在遗嘱里为子女安排好了信托财产。 3. You must trust in your own judgement. 你得相信自己的判断力. 4. Can you trust his account of what happened? 你能相信他对发生的事情所做的报告吗？', '名词: truster 过去式: trusted 过去分词: trusted 现在分词: trusting 第三人称单数: trusts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wherever', '[wer\'evər]', 'adv.无论什么地方 conj.无论在哪里', '1. I can fall asleep wherever and in any position. 我可以在任何地方任何位置睡着。 2. Remember you are a Chinese wherever you go. 不论你到哪里,记住你是中国人。 3. We\'ll go wherever you like. 你爱去哪儿我们就去哪儿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tub', '[tʌb]', 'n.桶；浴盆；<口>行进缓慢的旧船 v.装入桶；洗澡', '1. He scooped some ice-cream out of the tub. 他从桶里舀了一些冰淇淋。 2. He grabbed up the lid of the bran tub. 他把麦麸桶的盖子抓了起来。 3. I soaked in the hot tub for an hour. 我在热浴盆里浸了一个小时。 4. He will bath only after we fill the tub with toys. 他只有在我们在浴盆中装满玩具后才洗澡。 5. Do not tub for more than 5 min for cardiopathy sufferer. 心脏病患者浸泡时间不宜超过5分钟。', '形容词: tubbable 名词: tubber 过去式: tubbed 过去分词: tubbed 现在分词: tubbing 第三人称单数: tubs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('event', '[ɪ\'vent]', 'n.大事；事件；项目', '1. It was quite an event when a woman first became prime minister. 首次由女人任首相倒是件大事。 2. The new book was the cultural event of the year. 这本新书的出版是今年文化界的大事。 3. Don\'t get caught up in this event. 不要卷入这个事件。 4. This article discussed the events that led to her suicide. 这篇文章讨论了导致她自杀的一系列事件。', '形容词: eventless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('regardless', '[rɪ\'ɡɑːrdləs]', 'adj.不顾的；不注意的 adv.不顾', '1. He is regardless of the result. 他不顾虑结果。 2. He crushed the bloom with regardless tread. 他毫不在意一脚践踏了鲜花。 3. I protested, but she carried on regardless. 我极力反对，但她置之不理仍一意孤行。 4. They decorated the house regardless of cost. 他们不惜工本装修这栋房子。', '副词: regardlessly 名词: regardlessness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('human', '[\'hjuːmən]', 'adj.人的；人类的；有人性的；人本性的 n.人；人类', '1. The accident was caused by human error. 这宗事故是人为过失造成的。 2. It is beyond the confines of human knowledge. 这超出了人类的知识范围。 3. Her novel shows her keen insight into human character. 她的小说显示出她对人性的敏锐洞察力。 4. His cruelty suggests that he is less than human. 他的残忍表示他没有人性。 5. He was the only human on the island. 他是那个岛上唯一的人。', '名词: humanhood');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('approach', '[ə\'proʊtʃ]', 'v.靠近；接近；接洽；要求；达到；动手处理 n.途径；方法；接近；接洽；要求；路径；进场着陆；相似的事物', '1. He still had not the courage to approach her. 他仍没有勇气靠近她。 2. Such people as are friendly are easy to approach. 亲切之人容易接近。 3. She approached the bank for a loan. 她向银行要求贷款。 4. There is no one who even approaches his talents. 目前还没有谁的能力能与他媲美。 5. Narration should become a basic approach to preschool education. 叙事应是幼儿教育的基本途径。', '过去式: approached 过去分词: approached 现在分词: approaching 第三人称单数: approaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dull', '[dʌl]', 'adj.呆滞的；钝的；迟钝的；无趣的；暗的 v.变钝；迟钝', '1. Jack had all work but no play, making him a dull boy. 杰克只学不玩,这使得他成为一个呆笨的孩子。 2. It\'s impossible to cut a pineapple with such a dull knife. 用一把这么钝的刀子切菠萝是不可能的。 3. The mind becomes dull if the body doesn\'t get on exercise. 要是身体得不到锻炼,头脑也会迟钝的。 4. This book is rather dull. 这本书很枯燥。 5. The heating was turned up high to dull his audience\'s senses. 暖气温度被调到很高，以至于听众的意识变得迟钝。', '形容词: dullish 副词: dully 比较级: duller 最高级: dullest 名词: dullness 过去式: dulled 过去分词: dulled 现在分词: dulling 第三人称单数: dulls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('masterpiece', '[\'mæstərpiːs]', 'n.杰作', '1. The critics hailed his work as a masterpiece. 评论家们认定他的作品为杰作。 2. Do you think it was a masterpiece? 你认为这是杰作吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cartoon', '[kɑːr\'tuːn]', 'n.卡通；漫画；草图 vt.为 ... 画漫画', '1. The kids glued their eyes to the TV set, watching a cartoon. 孩子们目不转睛地盯着电视机看卡通片。 2. The man looks like a cartoon character with a plaster on his temple. 那人太阳穴上贴了一块膏药，看上去像个卡通人物。 3. This movie theater often shows the latest cartoon films. 这家电影院经常放映一些最新的卡通电影. 4. A newspaper cartoon is an amusing drawing, usually about some event in the news. 报纸上的漫画是一种风趣的图画，通常是针对某一件时事的。 5. The pen should draw cartoon using a pencil? 画漫画的笔应该可以使用铅笔吧？', '形容词: cartoonish 名词: cartoonist 过去式: cartooned 过去分词: cartooned 现在分词: cartooning 第三人称单数: cartoons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ox', '[ɑːks]', 'n.牛；公牛', '1. An ox pulls a wagon into the village. 有只牛拉着一台四轮车进入村庄。 2. The frequent, unreasonable whips angered the ox. 这种经常而无理的鞭打激怒了牛。 3. Farm owner feeds the ox with the wheat. 农场主用麦子喂牛。 4. The ox eats the grass on the lawn. 牛在草坪上吃草。', '名词复数: oxen');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sober', '[\'soʊbər]', 'adj.清醒的；稳重的；沉着冷静的；颜色暗淡的 vt.使清醒；使沉着 vi.清醒；冷静下来', '1. He was tipsy yesterday , but now is sober. 他昨天醉醺醺的,但现在是清醒的。 2. We should make a sober estimate of the situation. 我们对形势要有清醒的估计。 3. He is a very sober and hard-working young man. 他是一个非常稳重而勤奋的年轻人。 4. He talked with us in a sober and friendly fashion. 他以冷静而友好的方式同我们交谈。 5. He drank a cup of strong tea to sober himself up. 他喝下一杯浓茶以使自己清醒过来。 6. He sobered up quickly when he heard the terrible news. 他听到这个坏消息，马上就清醒过来了。', '副词: soberly 比较级: soberer 最高级: soberest 名词: soberness 过去式: sobered 过去分词: sobered 现在分词: sobering 第三人称单数: sobers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('observation', '[ˌɑːbzər\'veɪʃn]', 'n.观察；观察力；注意；评论', '1. The patient was kept under observation all night. 这位病人被观察了一整夜。 2. The law of nature was deduced from observation. 自然法则是从观察中推导出来的。 3. He is a man of little observation. 他是个观察力极差的人。 4. He was endowed with the power of acute observation. 他有敏锐的观察力。', '形容词: observational 副词: observationally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expend', '[ɪk\'spend]', 'vt.花费；消耗', '1. He lived high and expended largely. 他生活讲究，花费很大。 2. He has expended much time and energy on that experiment. 他已经花费许多时间、金钱在那实验上。 3. The soldiers expended all their ammunition in that fight. 士兵在那场战斗中用尽了所有的弹药。 4. I had expended much time on the work but they told me it\'s useless. 我花了很多时间在这件工作上，他们却告诉我说这是无用的。', '过去式: expended 过去分词: expended 现在分词: expending 第三人称单数: expends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dislike', '[dɪs\'laɪk]', 'v.不喜欢；厌恶 n.不喜爱；厌恶；反感', '1. We dislike to have anyone patronize us. 我们不喜欢任何人对我们以恩人自居。 2. What do you dislike most about this movie? 这部电影你最不喜欢什么？ 3. I saw everything I began to dislike, in retrospect. 我看见的一切都让我开始厌恶了，回想起来。 4. Jack showed his dislike plainly in scorching satire. 杰克以尖刻的讽刺直率地表明了自己的厌恶。 5. I saw everything I began to dislike, in retrospect. 我看见的一切都让我开始厌恶了，回想起来。', '形容词: dislikable 过去式: disliked 过去分词: disliked 现在分词: disliking 第三人称单数: dislikes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lawyer', '[\'lɔːjər]', 'n.律师', '1. His lawyer decided to take an appeal to a higher court. 他的律师决定向高一级法院上诉。 2. Nothing can weaken his resolve to become a lawyer. 什么也动摇不了他要当律师的决心。 3. A good lawyer can always find a loophole. 精明的律师总能找到漏洞。 4. The lawyer explained the new law to us. 律师向我们解释了新法律。', '副词: lawyerly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hers', '[hɜːrz]', 'pron.她的（she的物主代词）', '1. Your appearance is identical to hers. 你的相貌和她的一模一样。 2. This book is hers. 这本书是她的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('foam', '[foʊm]', 'n.泡沫；汗 v.起泡沫；吐口沫；愤怒；沸腾', '1. The sea was flecked with foam. 大海上涌起点点泡沫。 2. Foam rubber provides good insulation. 泡沫橡胶隔绝性能良好。 3. The fire extinguisher is filled with chemical foam. 这个灭火器充满了化学泡沫。 4. When the horse had finished the race, its sides were wet with foam. 这匹马结束比赛时，它的脊背被汗水湿透了。 5. When he poured the warm beer, it foam up out of the glass. 当他倒鲜啤酒时，啤酒泛起泡沫从杯中流了出来。', '过去式: foamed 过去分词: foamed 现在分词: foaming 第三人称单数: foams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cooperate', '[koʊ\'ɑːpəreɪt]', 'vi.合作；协力；配合', '1. I am so happy to cooperate with you. 很高兴与你合作。 2. I advise you not to cooperate with that deceitful businessman. 我建议你不要和那个不诚实的商人合作。 3. When buyers cooperate, they can make large wholesale purchases at a discount. 如果购买者联合起来,他们可以打折扣买大批的批发商品。 4. We need to cooperate perfectly to win the game. 要想赢得比赛，我们需要密切配合。', '名词: cooperator 过去式: cooperated 过去分词: cooperated 现在分词: cooperating 第三人称单数: cooperates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('barrier', '[\'bæriər]', 'n.栅栏；障碍物；屏障', '1. The ice skater rammed into the barrier. 溜冰者撞到护栏上了。 2. Heavy duties on imports and exports are a barrier to international trade. 进出口的高关税是国际贸易的障碍。 3. The Sahara Desert is a natural barrier between north and central Africa. 撒哈拉沙漠是北非与中非之间的天然屏障。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('satisfy', '[\'sætɪsfaɪ]', 'v.使满意；满足；使信服；清偿', '1. Some people are very hard to satisfy. 有些人是很难使其满意的。 2. We always satisfy our customers with good service. 我们总是以良好的服务来满足顾客。 3. We must satisfy the people\'s needs. 我们要满足人民的需要。 4. Output cannot satisfy the demands of the market. 产量无法满足市场需求。', '副词: satisfyingly 名词: satisfier 过去式: satisfied 过去分词: satisfied 现在分词: satisfying 第三人称单数: satisfies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('silk', '[sɪlk]', 'n.丝；丝绸；丝织品；丝绸衣服 vi.(玉米)抽穗丝 adj.丝的', '1. A cocoon is a kind of silk covering made by an insect. 蚕茧是由昆虫制造的一种由丝组成的外包层。 2. She has a scarf made of a triangular piece of blue silk. 她有一条用三角形蓝绸子做的围巾。 3. Their main exports are textiles, especially silk and cotton. 他们的主要出口货物是纺织品，特别是丝绸和棉布。 4. The silk is nice and soft. 这丝织品很柔软。 5. She wears a translucent silk gown. 她穿着半透明丝质长袍。', '过去式: silked 过去分词: silked 现在分词: silking 第三人称单数: silks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('determine', '[dɪ\'tɜːrmɪn]', 'v.决定；决心；确定；测定', '1. Chance will determine the outcome. 机缘将决定结果 2. I must now determine whether to meet him or not. 我现在必须决定是否要见他。 3. I am determined to find out the rights and wrongs of this matter. 我决心查明这件事的真相。 4. An inquest was held to determine the cause of his death. 为确定他的死因进行了审问。', '过去式: determined 过去分词: determined 现在分词: determining 第三人称单数: determines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('awe', '[ɔː]', 'n.敬畏；恐惧 vt.使敬畏；使惊惧', '1. The children stared at the teacher with awe. 孩子很敬畏地凝视着老师。 2. We all listened to the venerable scholar with awe. 我们都怀着敬畏之心倾听着这位德高望重的学者的讲话。 3. An unsought pathos came hand in hand with awe. 与恐惧相随而来的是一种意想不到的悲怆。 4. No difficulty could awe these young men. 任何困难都吓不倒这些年轻人。', '过去式: awed 过去分词: awed 现在分词: awing 第三人称单数: awes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('personnel', '[ˌpɜːrsə\'nel]', 'n.职员；人事部门', '1. The personnel are not happy to change these rules. 全体工作人员对改变这些规定很不高兴。 2. The company\'s main problem is the shortage of skilled personnel. 这家公司的主要问题是缺少有技术的人员。 3. Army personnel are often forbidden to fraternize with the civilian population. 军职人员常被禁止与平民百姓友好往来。 4. Personnel is organizing the training of the new menbers of staff. 人事部门正在组织新雇员的培训。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('angle', '[\'æŋɡl]', 'n.角度；角；观点 v.形成或转变角度；歪曲 v.钓鱼；谋取 Angle. n.盎格鲁人', '1. The rising sun is especially beautiful to look at from this angle. 旭日从这个角度看起来特别美。 2. Try looking at the affair from a different angle. 试从不同的角度来看这件事。 3. The two roads lie at an angle of about 45 degrees. 这两条路交叉成45度角。 4. We would like to hear your angle in this dispute. 我们想听听你在这场争论中的观点。 5. Angle the mirror so that you can see behind you. 调整镜子的角度,你可以看见你的后面。 6. He is keen on angling. 他喜欢钓鱼。', '过去式: angled 过去分词: angled 现在分词: angling 第三人称单数: angles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('advise', '[əd\'vaɪz]', 'vt.劝告；通知；忠告；建议 vi.提建议', '1. They advised her against marrying quickly. 他们劝她不要太快结婚。 2. Please advise us when the goods are dispatched. 请通知我们何时发货。 3. He can advise on how to learn English well. 他能就如何学好英语提出忠告。 4. I would advise you to keep out of the way when the teacher is rousting out the bad boys in the class. 我要忠告你，当老师训斥班上调皮学生的时候，你要避开一点。 5. The effective work of maintaining discipline is usually performed by students who advise the academic authorities. 而有效遵守纪律的学生们往往是那些经常给校方提建议的学生。', '过去式: advised 过去分词: advised 现在分词: advising 第三人称单数: advises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skilled', '[skɪld]', 'adj.有技能的；熟练的', '1. Unskilled workers usually earn less money than skilled workers. 无技能的工人通常比有技能的工人挣钱少。 2. The third wave includes Muslim refugees from Iraq, workers from the Indian subcontinent, students from South Korea, skilled Chinese and others. 第三波文化整合也包括了从伊拉克逃出来的回教难民，从印度来的工人，从南韩来的学生，有技能的华人移民等等。 3. The intricate machine requires a skilled operator. 这种复杂精细的机器须由技能熟练的人操作。 4. Fluent spoken English and skilled writen English. 熟练的英语口语及读写能力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rehearsal', '[rɪ\'hɜːrsl]', 'n.排练；彩排', '1. The symphony is in rehearsal now. 这支交响乐正在排练中。 2. This is not a concert, but more of a rehears. 与其说那是一场音乐会，倒不如说是一次排练。 3. Is there a rehearsal for the concert? 音乐会有彩排吗? 4. I had panic attacks during rehearsal. 彩排的时候我有过多次的恐慌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jury', '[\'dʒʊri]', 'n.陪审团；评委会 adj.临时用的 vt.挑选', '1. The case was tried before a jury. 此案是有陪审团参加审理的。 2. The jury brought in a verdict of guilty. 陪审团作出有罪的裁决。 3. The jury are unable to reach a unanimous decision. 陪审团未能达成意见一致的裁决。 4. The jury is about to announce the winners. 评委会即将宣布优胜者。 5. He was already called 4 times for jury duty. 他已经因为临时应急的义务被召唤过4次了。 6. Needless to say, the defense wanted McKinny on the stand, and they wanted the jury to hear selected portions of her tapes. 无需再说，被告方要求麦凯金到场，他们要陪审团听她录音挑选的部分。', '名词复数: juries 过去式: juried 过去分词: juried 现在分词: jurying 第三人称单数: juries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nothing', '[\'nʌθɪŋ]', 'pron.没有什么 n.没有；空；微不足道的事 adv.毫不；一点也不', '1. The sound faded into nothing. 声音逐渐消失了。 2. Two minus two leaves nothing. 二减二等于零。 3. His latest play is nothing. 他的新戏一文不值。 4. She is an interesting person but her husband is a real nothing. 她是个很有趣的人，但是她的先生却一无是处。 5. This will help you nothing. 这对你毫无帮助。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attendant', '[ə\'tendənt]', 'adj.伴随的 n.服务员；出席者；伴随物；侍从', '1. An unexpected accident is attendant upon carelessness. 粗心大意将导致意外事故发生。 2. Miseries are attendant on violence. 暴力往往会带来种种的不幸。 3. If you need anything, just ring for the attendant. 如果您要什么，就按铃叫服务员。 4. I asked the attendant to conduct him out. 我让服务员领他出去。', '副词: attendantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glass', '[ɡlæs]', 'n.玻璃；玻璃杯；玻璃制品 vt.镶玻璃 （复）glasses: 眼镜.', '1. I cut my hand on some broken glass. 碎玻璃割伤了我的手。 2. I ran up against a glass door and hurt my head. 我撞到一扇玻璃门上，把头撞伤了。 3. He put down his glass. 他放下杯子。 4. The milk slopped over the rim of the glass. 牛奶溢到玻璃杯外面来了。 5. Only three windows had been glassed. 只有三个窗镶上了玻璃。 6. He put his glass down on the circular table. 他把眼镜摘下来放在圆桌上。', '过去式: glassed 过去分词: glassed 现在分词: glassing 第三人称单数: glasses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fluctuate', '[\'flʌktʃueɪt]', 'vi.波动；动摇；起伏 vt.使动摇', '1. Fruit prices fluctuate with the seasons. 水果价格随着季节波动。 2. Some investors panic when stock prices fluctuate wildly. 当股票价格大幅波动时,一些投资者便开始恐慌起来。 3. While the psychological unbalance may fluctuate the individual\'s original philosophy and regular act tendency which make conditions for the naissance of aberrance. 而心理的失衡极大地动摇了个体原有的人生观和行为定势 ,为越轨行为的产生创造了条件。 4. Both the light and radio outputs fluctuate markedly. 光和无线电的输出都引人注目地起伏变化。', '形容词: fluctuant 名词: fluctuation 过去式: fluctuated 过去分词: fluctuated 现在分词: fluctuating 第三人称单数: fluctuates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('endure', '[ɪn\'dʊr]', 'vt.容忍 vi.忍耐；持久；持续', '1. I could not endure the insolence of his behaviour. 我不能再忍受他那傲慢无礼的行为了。 2. I cannot endure listening to that any longer. 我再也不耐烦听那一套了。 3. If help doesn\'t come,we must endure to the end. 如果没人来帮助,我们必须忍耐到底。 4. They vowed their love would endure forever. 他们海誓山盟地久天长。', '过去式: endured 过去分词: endured 现在分词: enduring 第三人称单数: endures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guest', '[ɡest]', 'n.客人；宾客；特别来宾；[动植物]寄生生物 v.做特邀嘉宾；做特约演员；客串；招待；做客', '1. They are coming to the party as my guests. 他们作为我的客人出席晚会。 2. These Indian guest are familiar with this book. 这些印度客人对这本书很熟悉。 3. She deleted our names from the guest list. 她把我们的名字从宾客名单中删去了。 4. She made a guest appearance on his TV show. 她在他的电视节目中出场客串。 5. She guested on several chat shows while visiting Britain. 她访问英国时做过几个访谈节目的特邀嘉宾。', '过去式: guested 过去分词: guested 现在分词: guesting 第三人称单数: guests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('precision', '[prɪ\'sɪʒn]', 'n.精确；精密度 adj.精确的', '1. The teacher laid emphasis on the precision of the translation from the outset. 老师从一开始就强调翻译准确性。 2. Your report lacks precision. 你的报告不够准确。 3. Every argument was stated with logical precision. 每一个论点都阐述得精确严密，符合逻辑。 4. These instruments are capable of very high precision. 这些仪器可以达到很高的精密度。 5. He spoke with pluperfect precision. 他用极为精确的话语发言。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elementary', '[ˌelɪ\'mentri]', 'adj.基本的；初级的；元素的', '1. He is ignorant of even the most elementary facts. 他连最基本的事实都不知道。 2. They lack the most elementary sanitary facilities. 他们缺乏最基本的卫生设备。 3. This is the elementary rules of social conduct. 这是社会行为的基本原则。 4. This elementary school is affiliated to a university. 这所小学附属于一所大学。', '副词: elementarily 名词: elementariness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('revolve', '[rɪ\'vɑːlv]', 'v.旋转；考虑；围绕', '1. The wheels began to revolve slowly. 车轮开始慢慢转动。 2. Their troubles revolve around money management. 他们的麻烦围绕在金钱处理上。 3. We must revolve the problem before giving an answer. 我们必须在回答之前把问题仔细考虑一下。 4. My life revolves around my job. 我的工作是我生活的中心。', '形容词: revolvable 过去式: revolved 过去分词: revolved 现在分词: revolving 第三人称单数: revolves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conflict', '[\'kɑːnflɪkt]', 'n.冲突；战斗；矛盾；斗争 vi.冲突；抵触；争执', '1. Both sides suffered heavy casualties in the border armed conflict. 在这次边界武装冲突中双方都遭到了重大伤亡。 2. He was wounded in the conflict. 他在战斗中负伤。 3. This is an irreconcilable conflict. 这是一个不可调和的矛盾。 4. He\'s got involved in a political conflict he can\'t extricate himself from. 他陷在一场政治斗争中不能脱身。 5. Your interests conflict with mine. 你的利益和我的冲突。', '形容词: conflictive 名词: confliction 过去式: conflicted 过去分词: conflicted 现在分词: conflicting 第三人称单数: conflicts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('respond', '[rɪ\'spɑːnd]', 'v.回答；响应；反应；反应灵敏；反响 n.[建]壁联；[宗]应唱圣歌', '1. I invited her to dinner but she did not respond. 我请她吃晚饭，但她未作回答。 2. The screen is sensitive and can respond to slight touch. 触摸屏反应灵敏,能响应轻微的触碰。 3. He tried to be amusing, but I didn\'t respond. 他试图逗乐,可我一点都没反应。 4. The car responds well to the controls. 这辆汽车操纵灵敏.', '名词: responder 过去式: responded 过去分词: responded 现在分词: responding 第三人称单数: responds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('signify', '[\'sɪɡnɪfaɪ]', 'vt.表示；预示；意味着；象征 vi.有重要性', '1. She signifies her disagreement. 她表示她不同意。 2. Do dark clouds signify rain? 有乌云是否显示要下雨? 3. A red sunset signifies fine weather. 红红的晚霞是晴天的预兆。 4. A fever usually signifies that there is something wrong with the body. 发烧通常意味着身体有点毛病。 5. It doesn\'t signify, so you needn\'t worry about it. 这无所谓，你不必担心。', '形容词: signifiable 名词: signifier 过去式: signified 过去分词: signified 现在分词: signifying 第三人称单数: signifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sting', '[stɪŋ]', 'vt.刺痛；使苦恼；欺诈 vi.叮；刺痛 n.刺；刺痛；讽刺', '1. Her ingratitude stung him. 她的忘恩负义使他痛心。 2. The smoke began to sting his eyes. 烟开始刺痛他的眼睛。 3. Those harsh words stung me bitterly. 那些严厉的言辞使我感到非常痛苦 4. They used to sting their clients. 他们过去常诈骗客户。 5. It is the nature of the scorpion to sting . 蝎子生下来就会蛰人。 6. A bee pricks the skin with its sting. 蜜蜂用螫针刺皮肤。', '副词: stingingly 过去式: stung 过去分词: stung 现在分词: stinging 第三人称单数: stings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('love', '[lʌv]', 'v.爱；热爱；喜欢 n.爱；热爱；爱情；恋爱；喜爱；情人；(网球)零分', '1. He swore to love her for evermore. 他发誓永远爱她。 2. I love my motherland. 我爱我的祖国。 3. The children love playing out in the open. 孩子们喜欢在户外玩耍。 4. \"A sweet temper\" is a figurative expression, but \"sweet coffee\" is not. \"甜蜜的性情\"是个比喻的说法，而\"甜咖啡\"则不是。', '过去式: loved 过去分词: loved 现在分词: loving 第三人称单数: loves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('criterion', '[kraɪ\'tɪriən]', 'n.标准；准则', '1. Practice is the sole criterion for testing truth. 实践是检验真理的唯一标准。 2. He thinks that the criterion of success is the ability to work joyfully. 他认为成功的检验标准是看能否愉快地生活。 3. We have a clear-cut criterion to go by. 我们有个可供遵循的明确标准。 4. The table shows the scoring for each criterion and criterion group. 上表显示每一准则和准则组别的评分。', '形容词: criterial 名词复数: criteria');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cart', '[kɑːrt]', 'n.【C】(二轮或四轮)运货马车；手推车 vt.<非正式>(用手推车)运送；(用力；粗鲁地)拖', '1. Don\'t put the cart before the horse. [谚]勿本末倒置。 2. The heavy cart rumbled down the street. 笨重的马车辘辘地在街上走过。 3. The cart is piled high with fruit and vegetables. 马车上堆满了水果和蔬菜。 4. They were shoveling coal into a cart. 他们在把煤铲进手推车。 5. We had to cart our luggage up six flights of stairs. 我们得把行李提着上六段楼梯。', '形容词: cartable 名词: carter 过去式: carted 过去分词: carted 现在分词: carting 第三人称单数: carts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('everywhere', '[\'evriwer]', 'adv.到处，处处；无论何处', '1. New factories are going up everywhere. 到处在兴建新工厂。 2. I hunted for my book everywhere. 我到处找我的书。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('torture', '[\'tɔːrtʃər]', 'n.拷问；痛苦 vt.拷问；使痛苦；曲解', '1. The use of torture must disgust any civilized person. 施用酷刑必为文明社会的人所不齿。 2. Torture always dehumanizes both the torturer and his victim. 严刑拷打往往使施刑者和受刑者都丧失人性。 3. She suffered the torture of toothache. 她因牙痛而痛苦。 4. He tortured his prisoners. 他拷打犯人。', '名词: torturer 过去式: tortured 过去分词: tortured 现在分词: torturing 第三人称单数: tortures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('meeting', '[\'miːtɪŋ]', 'n.会议；集会；汇合 动词meet的现在分词.', '1. The meeting will deal with these problems. 本次会议将就这些问题作出处理。 2. Our meeting in Beijing was later than I expected. 我们在北京的会面比我们预想的要晚。 3. Police were called in to break up the meeting. 出动了警察将集会驱散。 4. He had a brick thrown at him at that meeting. 那次集会时，他的头部被一块砖头击中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exhibition', '[ˌeksɪ\'bɪʃn]', 'n.展览；展示', '1. There will be an exhibition of the development of automobile industry in our country next week. 下星期将举办一个关于我国汽车工业发展的展览。 2. They came from afar to see the exhibition. 他们从远处赶来参观这个展览会。 3. The quiz was a good opportunity for the exhibition of his knowledge. 这次测验是他显示知识的好机会。 4. Such an exhibition of rudeness is absolutely unacceptable. 这样无礼的表现是绝对不能接受的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ankle', '[\'æŋkl]', 'n.踝；踝关节', '1. The doctor has taped up my swollen ankle. 医生用绷带把我肿起的脚踝包扎起来。 2. She stepped on a loose stone and twisted her ankle. 她踩到一块松动的石头上，扭伤了脚踝。 3. He gave a wrench to his ankle when he jumped down. 他跳下去的时候扭伤了足踝。 4. She broke her ankle weeks ago and it\'s still in plaster. 她的踝关节数周前骨折，至今仍打著石膏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('night', '[naɪt]', 'n.夜晚 adj.夜晚的', '1. Night began to fall. 夜幕降临。 2. We can see the stars at night. 夜晚我们可以看见星群。 3. With the setting of the sun, night comes silently. 随着太阳的落下，夜晚悄悄地来到。 4. Not many people want to be night owls. 不是很多人想当夜猫子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('treat', '[triːt]', 'v.对待；视为；探讨；治疗；处理；请客 n.款待；宴飨', '1. We should treat people and animals with humanity. 我们应该仁慈地对待人和动物。 2. Do not treat a naughty child rough. 不要粗暴地对待顽皮的孩子。 3. I decided to treat his remark as a joke. 我决定把他的话当作戏言。 4. Do not treat me as if I were a child . 不要把我当作小孩子看待。 5. A treat has been arranged for the old folk. 款待老人的事已作了安排。', '名词: treater 过去式: treated 过去分词: treated 现在分词: treating 第三人称单数: treats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('himself', '[hɪm\'self]', 'pron.他自己', '1. He is smart and can take care of himself. 他很精明可以照顾他自己。 2. His new house was built by himself, brick by brick. 他的新房子是他自己一块砖一块砖砌起来的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('steal', '[stiːl]', 'v.偷；窃取 n.偷窃；便宜货；(欺诈的)政治交易', '1. He was sent into prison for stealing. 他由于偷窃被送入监狱。 2. He stole a glance at the pretty girl across the table. 他偷偷地看了一眼桌子对面那个漂亮的女孩。 3. Despite fine acting by several well-known stars, it was a young newcomer who stole the show. 尽管几位名角演出都很出色,却未曾想竟让一名新秀抢尽风头。 4. The number of book steal from the library is large. 图书馆遗失的书很多。', '名词: stealer 过去式: stole 过去分词: stolen 现在分词: stealing 第三人称单数: steals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plastic', '[\'plæstɪk]', 'n.塑料；塑料制品；信用卡 adj.塑料的；可塑的；造型的；易受影响的；整形的', '1. Plastic is sometimes used instead of leather. 塑胶有时可以替代皮革。 2. Many items in daily use are made out of plastic. 有很多日常生活用品是塑料制的。 3. Consumers want to buy goods on the Internet using plastic. 顾客想要在网上通过信用卡购物。 4. A kind of plastic stuff is used to make the plates. 这些盘子是用一种塑料制造的。', '副词: plastically 名词: plasticity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('idea', '[aɪ\'diːə]', 'n.主意；想法；印象；意见；看法；观念；感觉；目标', '1. It\'s my idea to hold the party outside the house. 在户外聚会是我的主意。 2. It would be a good idea to go swimming in the pond. 到池塘里去游泳倒是个好主意。 3. I have no idea what I plan to be when I grow up. 我不知道长大以后要干什么。 4. I don\'t want anyone getting the wrong idea. 我不希望任何人有所误会。', '形容词: idealess');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plant', '[plænt]', 'n.植物；工厂；设备；设施 v.种植；设立；建立；安插；栽赃', '1. All plants need water and light. 所有的植物都需要水和阳光。 2. THe plant will come into bud in spring. 那种植物将在春天发芽。 3. After that we went on a tour of the plant. 然后我们参观了工厂。 4. We ordered it from a plant in Nanjing. 这是我们从南京一家工厂订购的。 5. April is the time to plant trees. 四月是种树的时候。', '形容词: plantable 过去式: planted 过去分词: planted 现在分词: planting 第三人称单数: plants');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intervene', '[ˌɪntər\'viːn]', 'vi.干涉；干预；介入；调停；插入；阻挠', '1. Don\'t intervene in the affairs of another country. 不要干涉别的国家的事务。 2. It\'s time that men of good sense and good will to intervene. 这该是那些头脑清醒和心地善良的人们出面干预的时候了。 3. You\'d better not intervene in their dispute. 你最好还是不要介入他们的争端。 4. I am powerless to intervene in the matter. 我对调停此事无能为力。', '形容词: interventional 名词: intervenor 过去式: intervened 过去分词: intervened 现在分词: intervening 第三人称单数: intervenes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('triumph', '[\'traɪʌmf]', 'n.凯旋；成就；胜利；欢欣 vi.战胜；庆祝胜利', '1. The winning team returned home in triumph. 球队凯旋而归。 2. The bridge is a triumph of modern engineering. 这座桥是现代工程的一大成就。 3. A smile of triumph lit up her face. 她的脸上闪露出胜利的微笑。 4. We finally won a diplomatic triumph. 我们终于赢得了外交的胜利。 5. Advancing culture is bound to triumph over declining culture. 先进的文化必然战胜没落的文化。', '过去式: triumphed 过去分词: triumphed 现在分词: triumphing 第三人称单数: triumphs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('park', '[pɑːrk]', 'n.停车场；公园；园区；(球类)运动场 v.停车；停放；置于', '1. He leaves his car in the hotel car park. 他把车停放在旅馆的停车场。 2. I often take my children to play in the park. 我经常带我的孩子们去公园玩。 3. Water, electricity, steam, natural gas and plant air will supplied by the park. 水、电、蒸汽、天然气、工业气体等由园区统一供给。 4. How to get to the baseball park? 棒球场怎么走？ 5. My car is parked over there. 我的汽车停放在那儿了。', '名词: parker 过去式: parked 过去分词: parked 现在分词: parking 第三人称单数: parks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grown-up', '[ɡroʊn ʌp]', 'adj.成人的 n.成年人', '1. He was brought up by his paternal aunt. 他是由姑姑抚养成人的。 2. In proportion to the baby\'s total weigt, its brain weighs seven times as much as a grown person\'s, it\'s muscles little more than half as much. 婴儿头部的重量占体重的比例是成年人的七倍，肌肉的重量占体重的比例则是成人的一半多一点。 3. A grown man like you shouldn\'t act like that. 一个象你这样的成年人不该做那种事。 4. Yet many grown people observe Halloween, too. 不过许多成年人也庆祝万圣节前夕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('internet', '[\'ɪntərnet]', 'n.因特网', '1. Internet plays a very important role in modern life. 互联网在现代生活中发挥非常重要的作用。 2. My brother doesn\'t know much about the Internet. 我哥哥对因特网所知不多。 3. The Internet has great attraction for young people. 因特网对年轻人有很大的吸引力。 4. You can obtain this information on the Internet. 你可以从因特网上获得这一信息。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('amateur', '[\'æmətər]', 'n.外行；业余爱好者 adj.业余（爱好者）的', '1. An amateur shouldn\'t play roulette for high stakes. 外行不该下大赌注赌轮盘赌。 2. You\'re a professional, but I am an amateur. 你是专业的,而我是业余的。 3. Don\'t let yourself be beaten by an amateur. 不要让自己给一个业余运动员打败了。 4. He is an amateur photographer. 他是个业余摄影爱好者。', '名词: amateurism');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('excursion', '[ɪk\'skɜːrʒn]', 'n.远足；短途旅行；【物】偏移，漂移，偏离；偏差，偏振', '1. The excursion was the high spot of our holiday. 我们那个假日的最大乐趣是远足。 2. We are planning an excursion to the blue mountain. 我们正在计划去蓝山远足。 3. I was roped in for this excursion before I knew it. 我不知不觉被拉来参加了这次远足旅行。 4. We shall make an excursion to Hangzhou this weekend. 这个周末我们将去杭州旅行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('breakdown', '[\'breɪkdaʊn]', 'n.崩溃；故障；衰弱；分类，明细；跺脚曳步舞', '1. His frequent depressions were the prelude to a complete mental breakdown. 他经常抑郁寡欢,后来精神完全崩溃了。 2. The old car rattled along again after a breakdown. 那辆破车在一次故障后又隆隆地行驶在路上了。 3. She suffered a nervous breakdown. 她患神经衰弱。 4. The accountant gave a breakdown of the expenses. 会计交出一份开支明细帐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chef', '[ʃef]', 'n.厨师；主厨', '1. The chef is not interested in Greek food. 厨师对希腊饭不感兴趣。 2. The chef sprinkle poppy seed on the cake. 厨师往蛋糕上撒罂粟籽。 3. I commended the chef on the excellent meal. I later wrote to commend him to his employer, the restaurant owner. 我称赞厨师做的菜味道好。随后我给雇用他的餐馆老板写了封信表扬他。 4. Dinner is in the hands of the chef. 晚餐由主厨负责。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alleviate', '[ə\'liːvieɪt]', 'vt.减轻；使 ... 缓和', '1. They alleviated the boredom of waiting by singing songs. 他们以唱歌来减轻等候的厌烦。 2. The doctor gave her an injection to alleviate the pain. 医生给她注射以减轻疼痛。 3. This medicine will alleviate your sore throat. 这种药会减轻你的嗓子痛。 4. He could only alleviate the sorrow by drinking. 他只能借酒浇愁。', '名词: alleviation 过去式: alleviated 过去分词: alleviated 现在分词: alleviating 第三人称单数: alleviates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('external', '[ɪk\'stɜːrnl]', 'adj.外来的；外部的；外面的；表面的 n.外观；外部；外界事物', '1. This news program only covers external events. 这一新闻节目只报道国外消息。 2. The external sector performance also improved significantly during the period. 在此期间,我国的涉外经济成绩斐然。 3. This force takes two forms, one internal and one external. 这个权力有两种形式:一种是对内的,一种是对外的。 4. All his injuries are external. 他受的伤都是外伤。 5. The external features of the building are very attractive. 这座建筑物的外观是很吸引人的。', '副词: externally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('front', '[frʌnt]', 'n.正面；前面；前线；【气象学】锋 vt.朝向；面对；对付 vi.面朝；掩护 adj.前面的', '1. The front of the postcard shows a picture of our hotel. 明信片正面是我们旅馆的图片。 2. Put the statue so that the front faces the light. 把雕像摆好，让正面向著光。 3. The front of the building was covered with ivy. 建筑物的前面爬满了常春藤。 4. The car in front of me stopped suddenly and I had to brake. 我前面那辆小汽车突然停住，我只好刹车。 5. This building fronts the railway station. 这栋建筑面朝火车站。 6. The hotels front onto the sea. 这些宾馆都是面朝大海。 7. The man sitting in front of me is asleep. 坐在我前面的人在睡觉。', '过去式: fronted 过去分词: fronted 现在分词: fronting 第三人称单数: fronts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('temporary', '[\'tempəreri]', 'adj.暂时的；临时的 n.临时工', '1. He suffered a temporary loss of memory. 他暂时丧失了记忆。 2. My love for you is not a temporary madness. 我对你的爱意,并不是暂时的疯狂。 3. The two parties procured a temporary agreement. 双方达成了临时协议。 4. I engaged a young woman as a temporary secretary. 我雇用一位年轻妇女当临时秘书。 5. The boss hired some temporary workers. 老板雇佣了一些临时工。', '副词: temporarily 名词: temporariness 名词复数: temporaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ill', '[ɪl]', 'adj.坏的；有病的；恶意的；引起痛苦的 adv.恶劣地；勉强地 n.邪恶；不幸；祸害；坏话', '1. There\'s one bad apple for every three good ones. 每四个苹果里就有一个坏的。 2. He was ill, but made out to be all right. 他病了，但却装着没有病的样子。 3. These nouns refer to the feeling or expression of deep-seated ill will. 这些名词指根深蒂固的恶意的感情或表述。 4. The new arrangement caused a lot of ill feeling. 新的安排引起了许多人的不满。 5. You should not speak ill of your friend. 你不应该说你朋友的坏话。 6. It is better to fight for good than to rail at the ill. 伸张正义，胜于嘲骂邪恶。', '比较级: worse 最高级: worst');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('derive', '[dɪ\'raɪv]', 'v.获取；得自；起源', '1. We shall derive much benefit from reading good novels. 我们将从优秀小说中获得很大好处。 2. We derive our sustenance from the land. 我们从土地获取食物。 3. One kind of vacation is camping, from which many Americans derive pleasure and benefit. 露营是一种度假方式，许多美国人从中得到乐趣，受益匪浅。 4. If we start some a year earlier, we shall derive the benefits a year earlier. 我们如果早开始一年,我们可以早得利一年', '形容词: derivable 名词: deriver 过去式: derived 过去分词: derived 现在分词: deriving 第三人称单数: derives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mild', '[maɪld]', 'adj.温和的；柔和的；宽大的；清淡的', '1. He has a mild nature. 他的性格温和。 2. He gave a mild answer, in spite of his anger. 尽管他十分恼火,他还是态度温和地回答了。 3. The coastal area has very mild winter, but by contrast the central plains become extremely cold. 靠近海岸的地区有很温和的冬天,相比而方,靠近中央的平原就变得非常寒冷。 4. The patient has a mild fever. 那个病人有些轻微的发烧。', '副词: mildly 比较级: milder 最高级: mildest 名词: mildness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tenant', '[\'tenənt]', 'n.房客；佃户；承租人；<律>占用者 vt.租赁；租借', '1. The tenant has not yet paid his rent. 房客还没有交付租金。 2. The desk was left by the previous tenant. 这张桌子是前面房客留下的。 3. He\'s a tenant farmer. 他是佃农. 4. There is a clause in the contract forbidding tenant to sublet. 合同中列有条款，禁止承租人转租。 5. I will tenant my building out during the summer vocation. 我会在暑假期间把房子租出去。', '过去式: tenanted 过去分词: tenanted 现在分词: tenanting 第三人称单数: tenants');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trigger', '[\'trɪɡər]', 'v.使发生；触发；使运行 n.扳机；起因', '1. Price increases will trigger off demands for wage increases. 价格上涨会激发人们增长工资的要求。 2. The odour of food may trigger people\'s appetite. 食物的香味能引起人的食欲。 3. A detonator is used to trigger an explosive device. 雷管用来引爆爆炸装置。 4. I pulled the trigger and the gun went off. 我一扣扳机，枪就响了。', '过去式: triggered 过去分词: triggered 现在分词: triggering 第三人称单数: triggers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stereotype', '[\'steriətaɪp]', 'n.模式化观念；典型；老一套；铅版 v.对…形成模式化的看法；使用铅版', '1. He doesn\'t conform to the usual stereotype of the city businessman with a dark suit and rolled umbrella. 他不像典型的城市商人那样，穿一身深色的套服、 带一把收好的雨伞。 2. He fits the stereotype of a scholar. 他是典型的学者。 3. The idea is an old-fashioned stereotype. 这观点是老一套了。 4. It\'s wrong to stereotype people. 把人看作都是一样的是错误的。', '形容词: stereotypic 副词: stereotypically 名词: stereotyper 过去式: stereotyped 过去分词: stereotyped 现在分词: stereotyping 第三人称单数: stereotypes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('range', '[reɪndʒ]', 'n.范围；射程；山脉；排；一系列；闲逛；炉灶；【数】值域，极差 v.排列；使…站在某一方；延伸；漫游；射程达到(某距离)', '1. The houses are sold out within this price range. 在这个价位范围之内的房子已售完。 2. It has come within the range of practical politics. 这就属于可实施性政治的范围了。 3. He used a whistle to decoy the birds within range. 他用口哨把鸟群诱至射程内。 4. She is still within range of my gun. 她仍在我枪炮的射程之内。 5. The shabby houses used to range along the road. 过去这路边破败的房子排成行。', '过去式: ranged 过去分词: ranged 现在分词: ranging 第三人称单数: ranges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('declaration', '[ˌdeklə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.宣言；宣布；申报', '1. The declaration was published in August 1687. 这份宣言是1687年8月公布的。 2. She read the declaration aloud for everyone to hear it clearly. 为了使大家都能听得清楚,她将宣言高声读了一遍。 3. These events led to the declaration of war. 这些事件导致了宣战。 4. Please show your customs declaration form. 请出示你的海关申报单。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('idiot', '[\'ɪdiət]', 'n.白痴；傻瓜；笨蛋', '1. What a stupid idiot! 真是个愚蠢的白痴！ 2. I didn\'t mince matters: I said he was an idiot. 我不讳言，我说过他是白痴。 3. He\'s a ruddy idiot. 他是个大傻瓜。 4. Don\'t treat me as if I were an idiot. 别把我当傻瓜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heap', '[hiːp]', 'n.堆；许多；<口>破车 vt.使成堆；装满；大量给予', '1. The books lay in a heap on the floor. 书堆放在地板上。 2. There is a disorderly heap of clothes in his room. 他屋里有一堆乱七八糟的衣服。 3. He fell down the stairs, landing in a heap at the bottom. 他从楼梯上摔下来，直跌到楼梯底部滚成一团。 4. We have a heap of work to do. 我们有许多工作要做。 5. The gardener began to heap up the fallen leaves. 园丁开始把落叶堆起来。', '过去式: heaped 过去分词: heaped 现在分词: heaping 第三人称单数: heaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accuracy', '[\'ækjərəsi]', 'n.准确(性)；精确度', '1. He\'s a man of accuracy and strict method. 他是个精细而严谨的人。 2. Accuracy is more important than speed in his new job. 对他的新工作，准确比速度更重要。 3. I can predict something with great accuracy. 我能很准确地预测某事。 4. It is impossible to say with any accuracy how many are affected. 无论如何也说不准受影响的有多少。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('independent', '[ˌɪndɪ\'pendənt]', 'adj.独立的；自主的；独自的；无偏见的 n.无党派者；独立派人士', '1. The former colonial possessions are now independent states. 以前的许多殖民地现已成为独立的国家。 2. You should learn to be independent of your parents. 你应该学习不要依赖父母。 3. Two independent investigators have reached virtually the same conclusions. 两个调查人员各自做出的结论简直完全一致。 4. He is an independent observer. 他是位无偏见的观察者。 5. The independent candidate is especially critical of the policy. 这位无党派候选人特别批评了该政策。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('publish', '[\'pʌblɪʃ]', 'v.出版；发行；公开发表', '1. Her book was published last year. 她的书去年出版了。 2. He published this book with his pen-name . 他以笔名出版了这本书。 3. Oxford University Press will publish a new magazine. 牛津大学出版社将发行新杂志。 4. Prime minister will publish the broadcasting speech this evening. 首相将于今晚发表广播演说。', '形容词: publishable 过去式: published 过去分词: published 现在分词: publishing 第三人称单数: publishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tiresome', '[\'taɪərsəm]', 'adj.令人厌倦的；讨厌的', '1. I had planned to go to your party, but you know I had to finish that tiresome paper. 我原本打算去参加你的晚会，可你知道我还得完成那令人厌倦的考卷。 2. His speech is really tiresome. 他的演讲实在令人厌倦。 3. Deliver me from such tiresome people. 让我离开这些讨厌的人们吧。 4. He can be a very tiresome child at times. 他有时候会是一个非常讨厌的孩子。', '副词: tiresomely 名词: tiresomeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wrench', '[rentʃ]', 'n.扳钳，扳手；猛扭；痛苦 vt.扭伤；挣脱 vi.猛扭；曲解', '1. It\'s hard to get at the spark plug without a proper wrench. 没有一把合适的扳钳，要抓住那个火花塞是困难的。 2. The knob broke off when he gave it a sudden wrench. 当他突然扭了一下球形把手，它便断了。 3. Leaving home was a terrible wrench for him. 他觉得离开家十分痛苦。 4. She couldn\'t stand the wrench of departure. 她受不了离别的痛苦。 5. Be careful. Don\'t wrench yourself. 小心点，别扭伤了。 6. I had to wrench the lid off the bottle. 我只好把瓶盖拧开。', '副词: wrenchingly 过去式: wrenched 过去分词: wrenched 现在分词: wrenching 第三人称单数: wrenches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('show', '[ʃoʊ]', 'v.证明；显现；展示；解说；指示；表示；表现；流露；带路；标示；描绘；陈列；证明；上映；出现 n.表演；展览；显示；行为；样子；景象；场面；表现', '1. The study shows an increase in the disease among the elderly. 这项研究证明这种疾病在老年人群中的发病率呈上升趋势。 2. Her laziness showed in her exam results. 她平时懒惰从她的考试成绩可以看得出来。 3. Let\'s show a picture to our audience. 要给大家展示一幅画卷啊。 4. She showed the technique to her students. 她向学生演示了那个技巧。 5. Diana is modeling for a fashion show. 戴安娜正在时装表演会上当模特。', '过去式: showed 过去分词: shown/showed 现在分词: showing 第三人称单数: shows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('offensive', '[ə\'fensɪv]', 'adj.令人不快的；冒犯的；侮辱的；与进攻有关的 n.攻势；攻击', '1. His hasty temper made him offensive. 他急躁的脾气使他令人讨厌。 2. His remarks were rather offensive. 他的话非常无礼。 3. The boss kicked him out for an offensive remark. 老板因为他说了一句冒犯的话就把他开除了。 4. She has been greatly annoyed by his offensive remarks. 他出言不逊,这使她很反感。 5. In meetings she always takes the offensive before she can be criticized. 在会上，她不等别人批评她而总是先发制人。', '副词: offensively 名词: offensiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fragile', '[\'frædʒl]', 'adj.易碎的；脆的；精细的；虚弱的', '1. Glasses are fragile and must be handled with great care. 玻璃制品易碎，必须小心轻放。 2. This glass plate is very fragile. 这个玻璃盘子很容易碎。 3. The fragile boxes arrived intact. 这些易碎的箱子完整无损地运到了。 4. Happiness is made of glass, it shines the brightest where it is most fragile. 幸福是玻璃做成的,它最脆弱的地方最闪亮!', '副词: fragilely 名词: fragility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hut', '[hʌt]', 'n.小屋；棚屋 v.在棚屋中隐蔽', '1. They tore down that old hut. 他们把那间旧草屋拆掉了。 2. The hut was made out of pieces of wood. 这小屋是用木板建造的。 3. The hut was made of poles covered with grass mats. 茅屋用木杆搭成，上面以草席覆盖。 4. We heard the rain spattering down on the roof of the hut. 我们听到雨滴滴答答打在小屋的顶上。 5. We can hut on the mountain tonight. 今晚我们可以住在山上的棚屋里。', '过去式: hutted 过去分词: hutted 现在分词: hutting 第三人称单数: huts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('also', '[\'ɔːlsoʊ]', 'adv.也；而且；同样地', '1. We should also take account of difficulties. 我们也应该考虑到困难。 2. London was also called the modern Babylon. 伦敦也被称为现代巴比伦。 3. This book is not only interesting but also good. 这本书不仅有趣,而且内容也非常好。 4. Tom has been to Japan, I have also been there. 汤姆曾去过日本，我也曾去过。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consist', '[kən\'sɪst]', 'vi.由 ... 组成；构成；在于；符合', '1. The United Kingdom consists of Great Britain and Northern Ireland. 联合王国由大不列颠和北爱尔兰组成。 2. How many players does a baseball team consist of? 棒球队由几名队员组成? 3. Matters consist of molecules, and molecules of atoms. 物质由分子构成，而分子由原子构成。 4. The islands consist of oyster reefs covered with a thin veneer of black mud. 由牡蛎礁构成的小岛上覆盖着一层薄薄的黑色软泥。', '过去式: consisted 过去分词: consisted 现在分词: consisting 第三人称单数: consists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('indignation', '[ˌɪndɪɡ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.愤怒；愤慨；义愤', '1. He could scarcely keep in his indignation. 他愤怒得难以自持。 2. Moral indignation is jealousy with a halo. 道德上的愤怒是萦绕着光环的嫉妒。 3. The atrocity caused widespread indignation. 那暴行引起了普遍的愤慨。 4. Such a humiliation filled me with indignation. 这种污辱使我感到极其愤慨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('service', '[\'sɜːrvɪs]', 'n.服务；发球；服役；公务部门；礼拜仪式；(车辆、机器等定期的)维修 v.保养；维护；提供服务；支付(借款)利息', '1. The volunteers for community service are doing a good job. 社区服务的义工做得很出色。 2. We all complain about the poor service in the hotel coffee lounge. 我们都抱怨饭店咖啡休息室的劣质服务。 3. You must run fast enough to return his service. 你必须要跑得很快才可能接起他的发球。 4. I\'d like to know something about badminton game,first,can you tell me about the service? 我想了解一下羽毛球比赛，能否先给我说说发球? 5. He suggested that my car should be serviced. 他建议我把汽车送去保养。', '过去式: serviced 过去分词: serviced 现在分词: servicing 第三人称单数: services 动词: serve');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('habitat', '[\'hæbɪtæt]', 'n.栖息地；产地', '1. The moth\'s habitat is being destroyed and it has nearly died out. 这种蛾子因栖息地正受到破坏，几乎绝种了。 2. The polar bear\'s habitat is the icy waters of the Arctic. 北极熊的栖息地是冰冷的北极海域。 3. I prefer to see animals in their natural habitat, rather than in zoos. 我宁愿观赏居住在自然栖息地里的动物，而不愿看关在动物园里的动物。 4. That country is the habitat of heroin. 那个国家是海洛因的产地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('it', '[ɪt]', 'pron.它', '1. It\'s Friday. 今天星期五。 2. It irks us to wait for people who are late. 等候迟到的人使我们厌烦。 3. \"Where\'s your car?\" \"It\'s in the garage.\" “你的汽车在哪儿呢?”“在车库里。” 4. The baby next door kept me awake. It cried all night. 隔壁的孩子吵得我睡不着觉。他整夜哭个没完', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beneath', '[bɪ\'niːθ]', 'prep.在 ... 之下；被...覆盖；低于...；不值得 adv.在下方；在底下', '1. They found the body buried beneath a pile of leaves. 他们在一堆树叶下面发现了那具尸体。 2. The earth lay beneath a blanket of snow. 大地被厚厚的白雪覆盖。 3. He is beneath his brother intellectually. 他在智力方面不如他兄弟。 4. Such behaviour is beneath contempt. 这种行为令人不齿。 5. Her careful make-up hid the signs of age beneath. 她的精心化妆掩饰了脂粉下面岁月刻下的痕迹。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slope', '[sloʊp]', 'n.倾斜；斜坡；斜面；斜率；斜线 vt.使倾斜 vi.倾斜；有坡度', '1. There is always a certain slope in a ship\'s deck. 船的甲板总有几分倾斜。 2. We slid down the grassy slope. 我们顺着草坡滑下去。 3. The hospital is on the eastward slope of the hill. 医院在小山的东坡。 4. There is no slope or angle to the croup. 在臀部没有斜面和角度。 5. They slope the grind so that the water can run away. 他们将地面铺得有坡度以便水能流泻。 6. The floor slopes badly here. 地板在这里倾斜得很厉害。', '副词: slopingly 名词: sloper 过去式: sloped 过去分词: sloped 现在分词: sloping 第三人称单数: slopes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sample', '[\'sæmpl]', 'n.样品；样本 vt.采样；取样；品尝，体验', '1. Thousands of people have written in to us for a free sample. 现已有数千人给我们来信索要免费样品。 2. What I need is nothing but a sample. 我需要的不过是一件样品而已。 3. The sample size would have to be quadrupled. 样本量必须增大三倍。 4. I\'ll send you some sample menus. 我会给您寄些菜单样本去。 5. We sampled the stuff and found it satisfactory. 我们抽验了这批材料，认为满意。', '过去式: sampled 过去分词: sampled 现在分词: sampling 第三人称单数: samples');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('everything', '[\'evriθɪŋ]', 'pron.一切；所有事物；形势；情况；最重要的东西', '1. Thank you for everything. 感谢你做的一切。 2. Money isn\'t everything. 金钱不是一切。 3. His standard for everything is excellence. 他对所有事物的标准是卓越。 4. I resent having to get his permission for everything I do. 我讨厌做每件事都要得到他的许可。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('district', '[\'dɪstrɪkt]', 'n.地区；行政区 vt.把 ... 划分成区', '1. This district used to grow cotton on a large scale. 这个地区过去大量种棉花。 2. We wish to be your agent in our district if the commission rate is favorable. 如佣金率优惠,我们愿意做你方在我们地区的代理。 3. He was elected the district attorney. 他被选为地方检察官。 4. The expressway rounded about the urban district. 高速公路环绕着市区。 5. The officials related have districted the city into three electoral districts. 相关官员把该市划分成三个选区。', '副词: districtwide 过去式: districted 过去分词: districted 现在分词: districting 第三人称单数: districts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('early', '[\'ɜːrli]', 'adv.早 adj.早', '1. They figured on your arriving early. 他们预料你会早到。 2. The apple trees are fruiting early this year. 今年苹果树很早结果。 3. Could you come back home early this evening? 今天晚上你能早回家吗？ 4. John will doubtless come early as he always does. 约翰无疑会像平时一样很早就来。 5. It\'s too early for getting up. 现在起床还太早。', '比较级: earlier 最高级: earliest 名词: earliness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('devil', '[\'devl]', 'n.魔鬼；淘气鬼；坏人；家伙；棘手的事 vt.困扰；添加辣味调料；给...做助手', '1. They believed she had been possessed by devils. 他们认为她是受魔鬼控制了。 2. He believes in devils and witches. 他相信魔鬼、巫婆这类事. 3. I bet you were a little devil when you were youger. 我猜你年轻的时候一定是个小淘气鬼。 4. My niece is a little devil. 我的侄女是个调皮鬼。 5. The little boy devils papa for a toy. 这个小男孩缠着爸爸买玩具。', '过去式: deviled/devilled 过去分词: deviled/devilled 现在分词: deviling/devilling 第三人称单数: devils/devils');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lesson', '[\'lesn]', 'n.教训；课，功课，课业；榜样，典范 vt.教训，告诫，训斥；给 ... 上课', '1. Such a lesson should be treasured in our memories. 这样的宝贵教训应该铭记在心。 2. That accident taught them a lesson. 那次事故给了他们一个教训。 3. I missed a lesson yesterday. 昨天我误了一节课。 4. This lesson pertains to marine animals. 这一课讲海洋动物。 5. The bitter lesson is branded on his memory. 那个惨痛的教训深深铭刻在他记忆中。', '过去式: lessoned 过去分词: lessoned 现在分词: lessoning 第三人称单数: lessons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attention', '[ə\'tenʃn]', 'n.注意；注意力；照料；留心；关怀；(口令)立正', '1. She soon becomes the centre of attention. 她很快成为大家注意的人物。 2. You should focus your attention on your work. 你应该把注意力放到工作上。 3. She gave her aging parents much attention. 她悉心照料年迈的双亲。 4. He didn\'t pay much attention to his surroundings. 他没有留心他周围的环境。', '形容词: attentional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preserve', '[prɪ\'zɜːrv]', 'v.保护；保存；保持 n.禁猎区；蜜饯', '1. It is highly important to preserve the environment. 保护自然环境至关重要。 2. It\'s the duty of the police to preserve the public order. 维护公共秩序是警察的职责。 3. You should preserve your papers for future use. 你应当把你的文件保存起来以备将来之用。 4. I tried to preserve my independence. 我试图保持自己的独立性。 5. No hunting is allowed in the preserve . 在禁猎区内不许打猎。', '形容词: preservable 名词: preservability 过去式: preserved 过去分词: preserved 现在分词: preserving 第三人称单数: preserves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('green', '[ɡriːn]', 'adj.绿色的；长满绿色植物的；环保的；无经验的；未成熟的 n.绿色；草地 vi.变绿 vt.使…变绿；使…恢复活力 Green. n.格林(姓氏)', '1. The paper turned green as if by magic. 这纸魔术般地变成了绿色。 2. The green fields came into sight. 一片绿色的田野展现在眼前。 3. The country is very green in spring. 春天的时候，乡村一片青葱碧绿。 4. Starch is an unharmful and green material. 淀粉化学品是一种有利于环保的绿色物质。 5. Green was the predominant color in the forest. 绿色是森林的主色调。 6. Our lawn grass does not green up until the middle of May. 我们的草坪要到五月中旬才变绿。 7. Mr. Green spoke highly of our city. 格林先生很称赞我们的城市。', '副词: greenly 比较级: greener 最高级: greenest 名词: greenness 过去式: greened 过去分词: greened 现在分词: greening 第三人称单数: greens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pear', '[per]', 'n.梨子；梨树', '1. This pear is rotten at the core. 这个梨子的果心腐烂了。 2. Would you like a pear? 想吃梨吗？ 3. This salad is made of apple, pear, potato and celery. 这份色拉是由苹果、梨、土豆和芹菜做成的。 4. There are many pear trees covered in blossom. 那里有许多开满花的梨树。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prey', '[preɪ]', 'n.牺牲者；被掠食者，猎物 vi.掠夺；捕食；使 ... 苦恼', '1. She fell (a) prey to melancholy. 她为忧郁所折磨。 2. She was easy prey for dishonest salesmen. 她很容易地让奸商敲了竹杠。 3. The lion seized its prey and ate it. 狮子抓住猎物，把它吃了。 4. The eagle seized its prey in a tenacious grip. 鹰将捕获物紧紧抓住。 5. In those far- off times Viking pirates used to prey on the coasts of Europe. 在那些遥远的时代里，北欧海盗经常在欧洲海岸一带进行掠夺。', '名词: preyer 过去式: preyed 过去分词: preyed 现在分词: preying 第三人称单数: preys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impose', '[ɪm\'poʊz]', 'v.强加；课征；强迫；征收(税款)', '1. I don\'t want to impose on you by staying too long. 我不想打扰你,不多耽搁了。 2. Do not try to impose your belief upon others. 别试图把你的信仰强加在别人头上。 3. We could not impose our own standards on others. 我们不能把我们的标准强加于他人。 4. He helped the Mongols impose taxes, interceding with the Khan to prevent reprisals when rebellions broke out. 因害怕在诺夫哥罗德人造反时遭到报复，他协助蒙古人征敛赋税。', '名词: imposer 过去式: imposed 过去分词: imposed 现在分词: imposing 第三人称单数: imposes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consume', '[kən\'suːm]', 'v.消耗；吃喝；毁灭', '1. His old car consumed much gasoline. 他的旧汽车耗油很多。 2. Each year Americans consume a high percentage of the world\'s energy. 每年美国人都消耗掉世界能源的很大比例 3. I\'m sure that Chinese people consume the largest amount of rice in the world. 我敢肯定,世界上中国人吃掉的大米最多。 4. I saw the flames consuming the whole building. 我看见火焰吞噬了整栋建筑物。', '过去式: consumed 过去分词: consumed 现在分词: consuming 第三人称单数: consumes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prudent', '[\'pruːdnt]', 'adj.谨慎的；有远见的；精明的', '1. Young as he was, he was prudent. 他虽然如此年轻，却很慎重。 2. We should be modest and prudent. 我们应该谦虚谨慎。 3. Prudent man always fits his standard of living to his budget. 谨慎的人总是使他的生活水平符合他的收支预算。 4. It\'s prudent to take a thick coat in cold weather when you go out. 在寒冷的天气下外出时带上件厚外套是谨慎的。', '副词: prudently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spite', '[spaɪt]', 'n.恶意；怨恨 v.刁难；惹怒；冒犯', '1. I\'m sure he took my parking space just out of spite. 我认为他侵占我的停车位肯定是有意和我作对。 2. They trampled his flowers out of spite. 他们出于恶意踩了他的花。 3. There is no gall or spite in my soul. 我内心对谁都没有怨恨或恶意。 4. He took my best toy just out of spite! 他仅仅出于怨恨拿走了我最好的玩具！ 5. The bad children left the room dirty to spite their maid. 那些坏孩子把房间弄脏来刁难女佣人。', '过去式: spited 过去分词: spited 现在分词: spiting 第三人称单数: spites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('purple', '[\'pɜːrpl]', 'adj.紫色的；辞藻华丽的 n.紫色；皇室', '1. The plant has a brilliant purple floweret. 那棵植物开着鲜艳的小紫花。 2. That girl likes to wear purple dresses. 那个女孩喜欢穿紫色的衣服。 3. He used to write purple prose. 他过去常写绚丽矫饰的散文。 4. His face turned purple with rage. 他气得脸色发紫。', '过去式: purpled 过去分词: purpled 现在分词: purpling 第三人称单数: purples');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fountain', '[\'faʊntn]', 'n.喷泉；源泉；储水容器；泉水 v.使像喷泉一样流', '1. She dabbled her fingers in the fountain. 她用手指在喷泉中玩水。 2. The parks of this city are famous for their ornate fountains. 这个城市的公园以其华丽的喷泉而著名。 3. Social life is the fountain of wisdom of writers. 社会生活是作家们智慧的源泉。 4. The brain is the ultimate fountain of ideas. 大脑是思想的根本源泉。', '过去式: fountained 过去分词: fountained 现在分词: fountaining 第三人称单数: fountains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overpass', '[\'oʊvərpæs]', 'n.天桥；立交桥 vt.超越；胜过；忽略', '1. Cross over the pedestrian overpass. 过人行天桥。 2. Overpass is so far away .Let\'s jaywalk. 天桥太远了，我们横穿马路吧。 3. An overpass bridged the highway. 立交桥跨越高速公路。 4. Would you have a look at the overpass in front of us. 你看前面的立交桥。', '过去式: overpassed/overpast 过去分词: overpassed/overpast 现在分词: overpassing 第三人称单数: overpasses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consequently', '[\'kɑːnsəkwentli]', 'adv.因此；所以', '1. The scandal being exposed, he was removed from office consequently. 他的丑闻被曝光了，他因此被调离了职位。 2. The company went bankrupt and consequently he lost his job. 公司破产,因此他失业了。 3. My car broke down and consequently I was late. 我的汽车坏了 4. The rain was heavy, and consequently the road was flooded. 雨很大, 所以路被淹没了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pretend', '[prɪ\'tend]', 'v.假装；装作；自以为', '1. She pretends that she likes them so that she can get their help. 她假装很喜欢他们，借以获得他们的帮助。 2. The young actor pretended to be Hamlet. 那个年轻演员扮演哈姆雷特。 3. She closed her eyes and pretended to be asleep. 她闭上眼睛,装作睡着了。 4. Surely he doesn\'t pretend to any understanding of music! 谅他不会自以为懂得什麽音乐吧！', '过去式: pretended 过去分词: pretended 现在分词: pretending 第三人称单数: pretends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feasible', '[\'fiːzəbl]', 'adj.可行的；可能的', '1. The plan did not seem feasible. 这个计划似乎没法实行。 2. It\'s quite clear that the electric car is technically feasible. 电动汽车明显在工艺技术上是可行的。 3. It\'s not feasible to follow your proposals. 按照你的建议去做是行不通的。 4. It\'s not feasible to dismiss him. 不可开除他。', '副词: feasibly 名词: feasibility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('setback', '[\'setbæk]', 'n.挫折；失败；退步', '1. He met with many a setback in his lifetime. 他一生中遭到过许多挫折。 2. This setback has drained away my keenness. 这次挫折削弱了我的热情。 3. Undaunted by his first setback, he decided to try once more. 不为最初的失败而动摇，他决定再试一次。 4. This latest arrest was just one minor setback. 最近的逮捕只不过是一个小小的退步。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('desolate', '[\'desələt]', 'adj.荒凉的；荒芜的；孤单寂寞的', '1. We saw few houses in the desolate valley. 在这荒凉的山谷里,我们很少见到房子。 2. The railway station became desolate in the war. 战争期间，这个火车站变得荒凉了。 3. Heavy rain will wash away the soil from desolate hills. 大雨将把泥土从荒凉的山丘上冲走。 4. This place is desolate of all vegetation. 这个地方不长草木。', '副词: desolately 名词: desolateness 过去式: desolated 过去分词: desolated 现在分词: desolating 第三人称单数: desolates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('insight', '[\'ɪnsaɪt]', 'n.洞察力；见识；深刻的理解', '1. I\'ve got an insight into the problem. 我对问题豁然开朗。 2. The book is filled with remarkable insights. 这本书很有真知卓见。 3. In this new book he hits off the American temperament with amazing insight. 在这本新书里，他对美国人性格的描写表现出惊人的洞察力。 4. Once human limits are breached, the person sees beyond the horizon of human insight, to reach a truly cosmic consciousness. 当局限被打破,人们的洞察力就可以超越凡人,看到宇宙真正的奥秘。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gas', '[ɡæs]', 'n.煤气；气体；汽油；空话 vt.使吸入毒气；毒(死)；给 ... 加汽油 vi.空谈；加汽油', '1. Gas is now widely used for cooking and heating. 现在普遍用煤气烧饭和取暖。 2. She lit the gas and gave the coffee another warm. 她点燃煤气，把咖啡重新热了一下。 3. Hydrogen and oxygen are gases. 氢和氧是气体。 4. Air is a mixture of gases. 空气是气体的混合物。 5. He was badly gassed in the war. 他在战争中深受毒气伤害。 6. The girls were still gassing when I left. 我走的时候，那些女孩子们还在胡扯。', '名词复数: gases 过去式: gassed 过去分词: gassed 现在分词: gassing 第三人称单数: gases/gasses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('descend', '[dɪ\'send]', 'v.下降；降临 v.传下来；遗传 v.突然袭击；突然拜访', '1. The sun descended behind the hills. 太阳下山了。 2. I wish that the prices can descend. 但愿物价会下降。 3. I didn\'t expect him to descend to personal abuse. 我没料到他会堕落到对我进行人身攻击的地步。 4. At 6:30 p.m. the tropical darkness descends. 在傍晚六点半的时候,热带地区的黑夜降临。 5. The custom has descended to our day. 这一习俗一直传到今天。 6. Armed thieves descended on the helpless travelers. 一群武装盗贼袭击了无依无靠的旅客。', '形容词: descendible 过去式: descended 过去分词: descended 现在分词: descending 第三人称单数: descends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('statue', '[\'stætʃuː]', 'n.雕像；塑像', '1. The statue is twice life-size. 该雕像大小为实体的两倍。 2. They decided to perpetuate the memory of their leader by erecting a statue. 他们为永远纪念那位领袖决定建一座雕像。 3. The statue was carved out of marble. 这座雕像是用大理石雕刻的。 4. The statue of Jefferson was big as life. 杰斐逊的塑像和真人一样大小。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('count', '[kaʊnt]', 'v.计算；视为；依赖；重要，有价值 n.计数；总数 n.伯爵（欧洲国家的贵族头衔）', '1. Material control and cycle count. 基本掌握物料控制及周期计算知识。 2. It\'s not humanly possible to count so quickly. 计算得这么快是人力无法做到的。 3. Fruity cocktails count as health food, study finds. 研究发现，水果鸡尾酒可被视为健康食品。 4. Since most countries already have too many laws, a pause for parliamentary reflection might count as progress. 大多数地区已经立了太多的法律，中止国会审议工作或可视为一种进步。 5. Take your blood count first, please. 请先做一次血球计数。 6. The count lived in that big house. 伯爵曾经住在那幢大房子里。', '过去式: counted 过去分词: counted 现在分词: counting 第三人称单数: counts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unlike', '[ˌʌn\'laɪk]', 'adj.不同的，不相似的 prep.不像，与…不同；与 ... 平时不同', '1. The two sisters are unlike in disposition. 那两姊妹性情不一样。 2. His new novel is unlike all his previous ones. 他新出的这部小说与他以前的不同。 3. Unlike a loan, a grant does not have to be repaid. 不像贷款，补助金不需要还款。 4. It was so unlike him to yield to such an irrational impulse! 他如此冲动，如此不顾理智，实在有失常态。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bird', '[bɜːrd]', 'n.鸟；禽', '1. That bird tried to peck me. 那只鸟想啄我。 2. The penguin is a flightless bird. 企鹅是一种不会飞的鸟。 3. Better be a bird in the wood than one in the cage. 宁为林中鸟,不作笼中禽。 4. The thrush is a kind of small singing bird. 画眉是一种小鸣禽。', '名词: birding 过去式: birded 过去分词: birded 现在分词: birding 第三人称单数: birds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('round', '[raʊnd]', 'adj.圆的；球形的；丰满的；完整的；整数的；不确切的；大量的；坦率的；严厉粗暴的 adv.环绕地；周长；调转方向；依次；到某处 prep.围绕；在另一侧；四处 n.一局(轮)；常规活动；巡视；圆形物；(由一人给大家买的)一巡饮料；一整片面包；一阵(掌声)；一发(子弹) v.绕行；弄圆；使成为整数', '1. He put the apples on a round plate. 他把苹果放在一个圆盘子里。 2. The earth is round because of gravity. 地球是由于重力而成为球形的。 3. Eustacia slowly drew up her sleeve and disclosed her round white arm. 游苔莎慢慢地把衣袖卷起，把她那只圆润丰满的白胳膊露出来了。 4. Give me a round dozen and I\'ll pay in cash. 给我一整打, 我将付现金。 5. He stood there looking all round. 他站在那儿环顾四周。 6. The earth travels round the sun. 地球围绕太阳运转。 7. The next round of peace talks will be held in Rome. 新一轮的和平谈判在罗马举行。 8. We rounded the corner at high speed. 我们以高速度绕过拐角。', '名词: roundness 过去式: rounded 过去分词: rounded 现在分词: rounding 第三人称单数: rounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shoulder', '[\'ʃoʊldər]', 'n.肩膀；肩部 v.承担；扛；肩负；(用肩)推挤', '1. The bullet wounded his shoulder. 子弹打伤了他的肩膀。 2. Her hand rested lightly upon his shoulder. 她的手轻轻地搭在他的肩膀上。 3. The bullet went clean through his shoulder. 子弹穿透他的肩膀。 4. We walked in the street shoulder to shoulder. 我们肩并肩走在街上。 5. The manager was ready to shoulder the blame. 经理愿意承担过失。', '过去式: shouldered 过去分词: shouldered 现在分词: shouldering 第三人称单数: shoulders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('repay', '[rɪ\'peɪ]', 'v.偿还；报答；还钱给', '1. He didn\'t have the wherewithal to repay the loan. 他没有钱偿还贷款。 2. You should repay principal and interest. 你必须偿还本金和利息。 3. I wish I can repay you somehow for your kindness. 我希望我能以某种方式报答您的好意。 4. We must do something to repay him for helping us. 我们得做点事以报答他的帮助。', '形容词: repayable 名词: repayment 过去式: repaid 过去分词: repaid 现在分词: repaying 第三人称单数: repays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gamble', '[\'ɡæmbl]', 'v.赌博；冒险；孤注一掷 n.赌博；冒险', '1. He spends all his time gambling in the casino. 他把时间都消磨在赌场的赌博上。 2. He gambled all his winnings on the last race. 他把赢得的钱全都压在最后一场赛马上了。 3. I wouldn\'t gamble on the weather being fine. 我可不指望天气能一直好下去。 4. Drive carefully and don\'t gamble with your life. 小心驾驶,别拿你的生命冒险。 5. The gamble paid off. 赌赢了。', '名词: gambler 过去式: gambled 过去分词: gambled 现在分词: gambling 第三人称单数: gambles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bone', '[boʊn]', 'n.骨骼；骨；核心 vt.除去骨头；往衣服里加撑条；磨光表面 vi.努力学习 adv.非常地；极其地', '1. Scientists have dated the fossils by their bone structure. 科学家根据那些化石的骨骼结构确定其年代。 2. Surgeons have made a great breakthrough in the bone operation. 外科医生们在骨骼手术方面取得了重大突破。 3. He broke a bone in his leg. 他摔断了一根腿骨。 4. The fish bone in her throat made her choke. 她喉咙中的鱼骨使她哽噎。 5. Next time, ask the butcher to bone the meat. 下次让卖肉的把肉里的骨头剔出来。 6. I must bone up on my French before we go to Paris. 在我们去巴黎之前，我必须刻苦学习法语－。 7. He is bone idle. 他非常懒惰。', '过去式: boned 过去分词: boned 现在分词: boning 第三人称单数: bones');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('confident', '[\'kɒnfədənt]', 'adj.自信的；有信心的；有把握的', '1. For my own part, being nice about appearance keeps me confident. 就我而论，注重仪表使我自信。 2. I\'m confident in the path I have chosen. 我对我自己选择的道路有绝对的自信。 3. Your encouragement made me more confident of my future. 你的鼓励使我对我的未来更加有信心。 4. One has to be confident in himself. 一个人一定要对自己有信心。', '副词: confidently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('collaborate', '[kə\'læbəreɪt]', 'vi.合作；通敌', '1. She collaborated with her sister/She and her sister collaborated on a biography of their father. 她和姐姐合作写父亲的传记。 2. We would ask you to collaborate with us. 我们愿意请你们和我们合作。 3. This supplier and I collaborate on certain points. 我与供应商有数方面或以上的合作。', '形容词: collaborative 名词: collaboration 过去式: collaborated 过去分词: collaborated 现在分词: collaborating 第三人称单数: collaborates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('means', '[miːnz]', 'n.方法；手段；收入；财产 v.意思是，意味（动词mean的第三人称单数）', '1. Are there any means of getting there? 有什么方法可以到那里吗？ 2. We express our thought by means of words. 我们用词句来表达思想。 3. He explored ways and means of solving the question. 他寻找解决问题的方法。 4. If other means fail we shall resort to force. 如果其他手段均告失败，我们将诉之武力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('creative', '[kri\'eɪtɪv]', 'adj.创造的，创造性的；创作的；产生的，引起…的（后接of）', '1. Painters are creative artists. 画家是具有创造性的艺术家。 2. The writing of poems, stories or plays is often called creative writing. 诗歌、小说和剧本的写作常常被称作创作。 3. He combines creative imagination with true scholarliness. 他兼有创造性的想象力和真正的学者风范。', '副词: creatively 名词: creativity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('narrative', '[\'nærətɪv]', 'n.故事；叙述 adj.叙述的；叙述体的', '1. She took up the narrative where John had left off. 她接着讲约翰未讲完的故事。 2. His adventure made an interesting narrative. 他的冒险是个有趣的故事。 3. Tatham was lost in wonder at the narrative. 泰瑟姆听了这个故事，惊奇得出了神。 4. Narrative makes up most of the book. 这本书的大部分篇幅都是叙述性的。 5. The lines form a prelude to his long narrative poem. 这几行诗是他那长篇叙事诗的序诗。', '副词: narratively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('carbohydrate', '[ˌkɑːrboʊ\'haɪdreɪt]', 'n.碳水化合物；糖类', '1. Carbohydrates provide our bodies with heat and energy. 碳水化合物给我们的身体提供热量和能量。 2. Athletes usually eat a high carbohydrate diet. 运动员通常吃高碳水化合物食物。 3. The receptor for hemagglutinin may be a carbohydrate. 其血凝素受体为糖类。 4. Of excessive adipose or carbohydrate food can bring about fatty liver. 过量的脂肪或糖类食物可导致脂肪肝。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grace', '[ɡreɪs]', 'n.优美；优雅；恩惠 vt.使优美；使荣耀', '1. She performed on the balance beam with much grace. 她在平衡木上表演得非常优美。 2. She was a beautiful girl with the grace and poise of a natural model. 她是一个美丽的姑娘，有着模特儿的那种优雅姿态。 3. By the grace of God their lives were spared. 蒙上帝恩宠 4. Fine paintings graced the walls of the room. 这些精美的绘画使四壁生辉。', '过去式: graced 过去分词: graced 现在分词: gracing 第三人称单数: graces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obtain', '[əb\'teɪn]', 'vt.获得；得到 vi.流行；通用；存在', '1. He failed to obtain a scholarship. 他没有获得奖学金。 2. At last, their company obtained the mining concession. 他们的公司最终获得了采矿权。 3. Those who were penitent obtained absolution. 悔过者获得了赦免。 4. They obtained a loan from the government. 他们从政府那里得到一笔贷款。 5. Your dress still obtains now. 你的这款套裙现在还很流行。', '形容词: obtainable 名词: obtainer 过去式: obtained 过去分词: obtained 现在分词: obtaining 第三人称单数: obtains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('after', '[\'æftər]', 'adv.以后；后来 conj.在 ... 以后 prep.在 ... 之后；在后面；关于；追赶；依照 adj.以后的', '1. They met in June and became lovers soon after. 他们在六月相遇, 不久就成了情侣。 2. The day after, he apologized. 次日，他道歉了。 3. They lived happily ever after. 他们後来一直生活得很幸福。 4. After dinner we paired off and went to dance. 饭后我们成双成对地跳舞去了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('basin', '[\'beɪsn]', 'n.脸盆；盆地；流域；水池', '1. This basin is made of iron. 这个盆子是铁做的。 2. He washed his hands in a basin. 他在盆里洗了手。 3. He first poured some water in the basin. 他先在脸盆里倒了一些水。 4. Wenshui lies in the west of Taiyuan Basin. 文水位于太原盆地以西。', '形容词: basinal');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reduction', '[rɪ\'dʌkʃn]', 'n.减少；降低；减价；(化学)还原反应；(数学)约分', '1. This represents a reduction of 5%in real terms. 这相当于实际减少了 5%25。 2. The reduction of unemployment should be paramount. 降低失业率应是头等大事。 3. In view of our long-standing business relations, we can consider a price reduction. 鉴于你我双方长期的业务关系，我们可以考虑减价。 4. Can you give me a 5% reduction? 你能给我打九五折吗？', '形容词: reductional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('identify', '[aɪ\'dentɪfaɪ]', 'vt.鉴定；识别，辨认出，认出；认明；把…看成一样 vi.认同；感同身受', '1. Identify how the incident occurred. 鉴定事故如何出现。 2. The test can identify the presence of abnormalities in the unborn child. 这项化验能鉴定胎儿是否有不正常现象。 3. The markings are so blurred that it is difficult to identify. 标记模糊不清，难以识别。 4. Please identify the registered trademark. 请认明注册商标。 5. I found it hard to identify with any of the characters in the film. 我对这部影片里的任何角色都难以认同。', '形容词: identifiable 副词: identifiably 名词: identifier 过去式: identified 过去分词: identified 现在分词: identifying 第三人称单数: identifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fix', '[fɪks]', 'v.使 ... 固定；修理，处理，解决；确定；准备；操纵 n.困境；(船只、飞机等的)定方位；贿赂；（暂时的）解决方法；理解', '1. He fixed a shelf to the wall. 他把架子装在墙上。 2. My watch has stopped it needs fixing. 我的表停了,需要修理了。 3. Have you fixed on a date for the wedding? 你们选定结婚日期了吗? 4. Give me a couple of minutes while I fix my hair. 给我几分钟时间，我在梳理头发。 5. We are in a real fix - there is nobody to look after the baby. 我们真的处于困境——没人照顾婴儿。', '形容词: fixable 名词: fixer 过去式: fixed 过去分词: fixed 现在分词: fixing 第三人称单数: fixes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('form', '[fɔːrm]', 'n.形式；形状；表格；良好的健康状态；表现状态；常规 v.形成；建立', '1. Playing basketball is one form of physical exercise. 打篮球是体育活动的一种形式。 2. The form of a building grows out of its use. 建筑物的形式取决于建筑物的用途。 3. It has the irregular form of an ink blot. 它具有不规则的水渍形状。 4. He is filling in a form. 他正在填写一张表格。 5. A plan began to form in his head. 一项计划在他脑子中形成。', '形容词: formable 名词: formability 过去式: formed 过去分词: formed 现在分词: forming 第三人称单数: forms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extinguish', '[ɪk\'stɪŋɡwɪʃ]', 'vt.熄灭；扑灭；消灭；使破灭；偿清', '1. Smoking is forbidden. Please extinguish your cigarettes. 吸烟是禁止的，请你把烟熄掉。 2. They tried to extinguish the flames. 他们竭力要把火焰扑灭。 3. The dictator wanted to extinguish all of his opposition in one go. 这位独裁者想一口气消灭所有对手。 4. Nothing could extinguish his faith in human nature. 没有什么能使他丧失对人性的信心。', '形容词: extinguishable 名词: extinguishment 过去式: extinguished 过去分词: extinguished 现在分词: extinguishing 第三人称单数: extinguishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('paw', '[pɔː]', 'n.脚爪；爪子；<口>手 v.以蹄扒；抓；粗鲁地摸；翻找', '1. The dog pressed his paw on the latch to let himself in. 那狗用脚爪按住门闩把自己放进来。 2. The kitten has very soft paws. 小猫的爪子很软。 3. The dog gave a yelp when I trod on its paw. 我踩了那狗的爪子，它嚎叫了一声。 4. The dog was howling its paw was hurt. 那条狗在嗥叫--它的爪子受伤了。 5. The bull pawed the ground before charging. 那头牛用蹄刨着地准备出击。', '名词: pawer 过去式: pawed 过去分词: pawed 现在分词: pawing 第三人称单数: paws');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reality', '[ri\'æləti]', 'n.真实；现实；实际', '1. He describes the scene with startling reality. 他对那景象的描述逼真得令人惊讶。 2. I try to convince him of the reality of the danger. 我试图使他相信危险的确存在。 3. His plans were transformed overnight into reality. 他的计划迅速变为现实。 4. This is the just the bitter reality of wars in Iraq. 这就是伊拉克战争的惨痛现实。', '名词复数: realities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('technical', '[\'teknɪkl]', 'adj.技术的；专业的；工艺的', '1. On technical matters, I defer to the experts. 在技术问题上，我遵从专家的意见。 2. The flight was delayed owing to technical reasons. 这次飞行由于技术的原因而被推迟。 3. This book is too technical for me. 对我来说，这本书太专业了。 4. The article is full of technical terms. 这篇文章满篇皆是专业术语。', '副词: technically 名词: technicalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brief', '[briːf]', 'adj.短暂的；短期的；简短的；扼要的 n.摘要；案件陈述 vt.作…的概述；（向…）简单介绍', '1. There was a brief pause in the conversation. 对话中有短暂的停顿。 2. We have a tight schedule for your brief visit. I hope you don\'t mind. 对您短暂的访问,我们为您安排的日程很紧,希望您不介意。 3. In the beginning, the teacher gave us a brief introduction about the subject. 开始时,老师给我们做了关于这门课程的简短介绍。 4. I don\'t want to keep you long, so let me be brief. 我不想浪费大家的时间,就简明扼要地讲几句吧。 5. He drew up a brief for his speech. 他起草了一份讲话的摘要。 6. The chairman will brief the Board on the most recent developments. 主席将向董事会概述最近的发展。', '副词: briefly 比较级: briefer 最高级: briefest 名词: briefer 过去式: briefed 过去分词: briefed 现在分词: briefing 第三人称单数: briefs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disperse', '[dɪ\'spɜːrs]', 'v.分散；散开', '1. The police dispersed the crowd. 警方驱散群众。 2. The wind dispersed the cloud from the sky. 风吹散了天上的云。 3. The enemy had to disperse and hide in caves. 敌人不得不分散藏身于洞穴之中。 4. The crowd dispersed. 人群纷纷散开。', '形容词: dispersible 副词: dispersedly 名词: dispersant 过去式: dispersed 过去分词: dispersed 现在分词: dispersing 第三人称单数: disperses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tomato', '[tə\'meɪtoʊ]', 'n.西红柿；蕃茄', '1. Would you like some tomato paste? 你要西红柿酱吗？ 2. His shirt was stained with tomato juice. 我的衬衣被西红柿汁污染了。 3. Most tomatoes are red when ripe, but some kinds are yellow. 大多数西红柿成熟时是红色的，但有些品种是黄色的。 4. Is a tomato a fruit or a vegetable? 蕃茄是水果还是蔬菜?', '名词复数: tomatoes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('casualty', '[\'kæʒuəlti]', 'n.事故；伤亡者；伤亡人数；<英>急诊室', '1. The cottage was a casualty of the forest fire. 那小屋被森林大火烧毁。 2. She read through the casualty list anxiously. 她忧虑地把伤亡人员名单从头到尾看了一遍。 3. The casualty of the traffic accident was a doleful record. 这一交通事故地伤亡人数是一个令人伤心的记录.', '名词复数: casualties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('depth', '[depθ]', 'n.深度；深刻；深奥；深；厚度', '1. The young man dived to a depth of 40 feet. 那个青年人潜到四十尺的深度。 2. Her latest poem has remarkable depth. 她最近的那首诗极有深度。 3. He is admired for the depth of his perception. 他因理解深刻而很受赏识。 4. The child is being taught subjects that are beyond his depth. 现在教给孩子的学科都过于深奥。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thief', '[θiːf]', 'n.贼；小偷', '1. His enemies labelled him a thief. 他的敌人称他为贼。 2. The thief was confined in a prison. 窃贼被关押在监狱里。 3. The police set a trap to catch the thief. 警察设下了捉拿窃贼的圈套。 4. The thief was caught red-handed. 小偷被当场抓住了。', '名词复数: thieves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('knock', '[nɑːk]', 'v.敲击；互撞；攻击 n.敲；敲门；敲打', '1. Someone is knocking at the door. 有人在敲门。 2. One may knock to signal one\'s presence to others. 可以用敲击发出的声音向别人表明自己的存在。 3. He knocked a big hole in the wall. 他把墙撞出了一个大洞。 4. I am so hurried as to knock into my teacher. 我如此匆忙以至于撞到老师身上。 5. There was a knock at the window. 有人敲了一下窗户。', '过去式: knocked 过去分词: knocked 现在分词: knocking 第三人称单数: knocks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kite', '[kaɪt]', 'n.风筝；鸢 n.空头支票 v.用空头支票骗人；使上升', '1. The children are flying kites. 孩子们在放风筝。 2. A boy is flying a kite in the piazza. 一个小男孩在阳台上放风筝。 3. I looked up into the sky and saw the kite become smaller and smaller. 我遥望天空，只见风筝越来越小。 4. A kite will never be a good hawk. 鸢永不会变成隼。 5. She got caught kite flying in Philadelphia. 她在费城到处开空头支票时被抓住。 6. The bill was due before payday, so I had to kite the check. 工资还没发，帐单就到期了，于是我只好开空头支票。', '过去式: kited 过去分词: kited 现在分词: kiting 第三人称单数: kites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exquisite', '[ɪk\'skwɪzɪt]', 'adj.精挑细选的；精致的；细腻的；强烈的 n.过分在意外表着装的人', '1. The hostess had exquisite taste in clothes. 女主人对衣著十分讲究。 2. The girl came up with a set of exquisite stamps. 那姑娘拿出一套精美的邮票。 3. Her skirt has very exquisite lace. 她的裙子有非常精致的花边。 4. The bracelet was made with exquisite workmanship. 这只手镯做得巧夺天工。', '副词: exquisitely 名词: exquisiteness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mystery', '[\'mɪstri]', 'n.谜，神秘；奥秘；秘密；神秘的人或事物；推理小说（戏剧）', '1. His past is enveloped in a shroud of mystery. 他过去的经历笼罩着神秘气氛。 2. The dark trees lent an air of mystery to the scene. 阴暗的树林给景色带来几分神秘。 3. She proposed a possible solution to the mystery. 她提出了对这个奥秘的一种可能的解答。 4. The mystery has now come to light. 这个秘密现在已被揭开了。', '名词复数: mysteries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('permission', '[pər\'mɪʃn]', 'n.许可；允许；同意', '1. They entered the area without permission. 他们未经许可擅入该地。 2. You were wrong to take the car without permission. 你未得许可就把汽车开走是不应该的。 3. You must ask permission if you want to leave early. 如果你想早走的话，必须得到允许。 4. Do I have your permission to change the date? 您允许我改变一下日期吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('earthquake', '[\'ɜːrθkweɪk]', 'n.地震', '1. The earthquake rocked the houses. 地震震动房屋。 2. There has been a dreadful earthquake in Iran. 伊朗发生了一次可怕的地震。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lavatory', '[\'lævətɔːri]', 'n.盥洗室；厕所', '1. I am sorry to bother you,but the lavatory drain be block. 对不起打扰您，但是盥洗室的排水管堵塞了。 2. The use of the lavatory has been suspended during take-off. 在飞机起飞期间，盥洗室暂停使用。 3. The lavatory windows are made of translucent glass. 厕所窗户是用半透明玻璃做的。 4. There is a gentleman\'s lavatory on the ground floor. 一层有男厕所。', '名词复数: lavatories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recreation', '[ˌrekri\'eɪʃn]', 'n.消遣；娱乐', '1. In other words, we had better take sufficient recreation to relax after work. 换句话说，我们最好工作后，消遣消遣来轻松一下。 2. Art is both creation and recreation. 艺术是创作，同时也是消遣。 3. Some films combine education with recreation . 有些影片把教育同娱乐融合在一起。 4. Our city needs more facilities for recreation. 我们城市需要更多的娱乐设施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bare', '[ber]', 'adj.赤裸的；空的；仅有的；贫瘠的，荒芜的 vt.使裸露；暴露', '1. The fierce sun parched the bare earth. 灼热的阳光炙烤着光秃秃的大地。 2. The boy likes to walk on the sand with bare feet. 这男孩喜欢赤脚在沙滩上走。 3. The little room was almost bare of furniture. 这个小房间几乎没有什么家俱。 4. A bare word would be enough for me. 对我来说一句话就够了。 5. He bared the tree of its bark. 他剥光树皮。', '比较级: barer 最高级: barest 名词: bareness 过去式: bared 过去分词: bared 现在分词: baring 第三人称单数: bares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clothes', '[kloʊðz]', 'n.服装；衣服', '1. She has good taste in clothes. 她对服装有很好的审美眼光。 2. It might be appropriate to wear traditional clothes on special occasions. 在某些特定的场合,我们适合穿传统服装。 3. I washed many clothes with my washer last night. 我昨晚用洗衣机洗了很多衣服。 4. Plain, simple clothes are appropriate for school wear. 简单朴素的衣服适合在学校里穿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('knife', '[naɪf]', 'n.刀 v.用刀切割', '1. He cleaved an apple with a knife. 他用一把刀子将苹果切开。 2. I picked up the knife and threw it out of the window. 我拿起了那把刀，把它扔到了窗外。 3. His cheek was badly scarred by a knife cut. 他的面颊上留有严重的刀疤。 4. The victim had been knifed in the chest. 受害人胸部中刀。', '名词: knifer 名词复数: knives 过去式: knifed 过去分词: knifed 现在分词: knifing 第三人称单数: knifes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surgeon', '[\'sɜːrdʒən]', 'n.外科医生', '1. The surgeon has performed the operation. 外科医生做了手术。 2. The surgeon operated on her for appendicitis. 外科医生为她做阑尾切除手术。 3. The surgeon asked him if he felt nervous. 外科医生问他是否感到紧张。 4. He is reputed as the best surgeon in Paris. 他被认为是巴黎最好的外科医生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mend', '[mend]', 'vt.修理；修补；改进 vi.改过自新；改进；痊愈 n.修补；改进；修补处', '1. We need an electrician to mend the iron. 我们要请电工修理熨斗。 2. It won\'t take long to mend the car. 修理这辆汽车用不了很长时间。 3. He sent for someone to mend the broken window. 他叫人来修补破窗子。 4. You\'ll have to mend your ways if you want to be successful in your job. 如果你想在你的工作中取得成绩的话，你一定要有所改进。 5. It is never too late to mend. 改过不嫌晚。 6. The mends were almost invisible. 修补过的地方几乎看不出来。', '形容词: mendable 名词: mender 过去式: mended 过去分词: mended 现在分词: mending 第三人称单数: mends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tedious', '[\'tiːdiəs]', 'adj.单调乏味的；沉闷的', '1. The tedious job simply ate me up. 那单调乏味的工作简直把我烦死了。 2. He told me a tedious story. 他给我讲了一个冗长乏味的故事。 3. He is an exceedingly tedious fellow. 他是一个非常令人生厌的家伙。 4. How can he give us such a tedious lecture. 他怎么能做这么沉闷乏味的演讲。', '副词: tediously 名词: tediousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dissipate', '[\'dɪsɪpeɪt]', 'v.驱散；消散；散去；浪费；挥霍；放荡', '1. The sun dissipated the mist. 太阳驱散了雾。 2. Her son\'s letter dissipated all her fears and anxiety. 她儿子的来信消除了她一切恐惧和焦虑。 3. The crowd dissipated soon after the police arrived. 在警察到达之后，人群很快散去了。 4. He soon dissipated his fortune. 他很快就把财产浪费光了。', '形容词: dissipative 名词: dissipater 过去式: dissipated 过去分词: dissipated 现在分词: dissipating 第三人称单数: dissipates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blackboard', '[\'blækbɔːrd]', 'n.黑板', '1. Who\'s rubbed my figures off the blackboard? 谁把我写在黑板上的数字擦掉了? 2. The blackboard is in the front of the classroom. 黑板在教室的前面。 3. Please raise your head and look at the blackboard. 请抬起头来，看黑板。 4. The teacher wrote on the blackboard with a piece of chalk. 老师用一支粉笔在黑板上写字。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('committee', '[kə\'mɪti]', 'n.委员会', '1. The committee meets at three today. 委员会今天三点开会。 2. Moderates have displaced the extremists on the committee. 在委员会中，稳健派人士取代了激进派人士。 3. Some members of the committee expressed reservations about the proposal. 委员会一些成员对这项提议持保留态度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('moral', '[\'mɔːrəl]', 'adj.道德的；精神上的 n.寓意；道德；品行；伦理', '1. She regards his moral faults with charity. 她宽恕他的品行不端。 2. We differ about moral standards. 我们对道德标准看法不一致。 3. His behavior transgressed the moral rules of the social conduct. 他的行为违背了社会行为的道德准则。 4. It comprises two main sets of rights: the economic rights and the moral rights. 版权包括两种主要的权利:经济权利和精神权利。 5. The moral of this story is ‘Better late than never\'. 这个故事的寓意是｀迟做总比不做好＇.', '副词: morally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('favor', '[\'feɪvə]', 'n.偏爱；好意；特权；赞成 vt.偏爱；给予；支持；关心；利于；长得像', '1. He did all he could to win his favor. 他尽其所能去赢得他的好感。 2. Could you do me a big favor? 能否请你帮我个忙？ 3. I always grant favors to my friends. 我总是给朋友以特殊照顾。 4. To a certain extent, I\'m in favor of your project. 从某种程度上说,我赞成你的方案。 5. A mother mustn\'t favor one of her children more than the others. 母亲不应对任何一个儿女有所偏爱。', '副词: favoringly 名词: favorer 过去式: favored 过去分词: favored 现在分词: favoring 第三人称单数: favors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('painter', '[\'peɪntər]', 'n.画家；油漆匠', '1. He is an amateur painter. 他是一个业余画家。 2. The painter stretched the canvas on a frame. 画家把油画布紧绷在画框上。 3. He was an unknown painter one year ago. 一年前，他还是一个不为人知的画家。 4. The painter pitched the ladder against the wall. 油漆匠将梯子斜靠在墙上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('speaker', '[\'spiːkər]', 'n.说话者；发言者；说某种语言者；扬声器', '1. The speaker was boring everybody. 说话者令每个人生厌。 2. These gestures are extremely important as they virtually negate what the speaker says. 这些肢体动作极其重要，因为它们几乎否定掉说话者所说的话。 3. The speaker sawed the air as he cried loudly. 发言者一边挥舞手臂一边大声叫喊。 4. I call on Mr. Oates, the first speaker on my list. 现在请名单上第一位发言者奥茨先生讲话。', '名词: speakership');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('insulate', '[\'ɪnsəleɪt]', 'vt.使绝缘；隔离', '1. We can insulate a live wire with rubber. 我们可用橡胶使带电的电线绝缘。 2. Rubber is used to insulate electric wires. 橡胶被用来使电线与外界绝缘。 3. Her parents tried to insulate her from dangerous influences. 她的父母试图把她与危险的影响隔绝。 4. It is important to insulate the furnace from any neighbouring woodwork with brick and asbestos. 用砖和石棉把炉子与周围所有的木制品隔开，这很重要。', '过去式: insulated 过去分词: insulated 现在分词: insulating 第三人称单数: insulates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lumber', '[\'lʌmbər]', 'n.木材；木料 v.伐木 vi.缓慢地移动 vt.拖累', '1. I followed the road down past the piles of lumber. 我穿过成堆木材，沿着路走下去。 2. Iron mined in order to topple trees for lumber. 开采铁矿则是为了砍伐树木以获取木材。 3. They slapped together a cabin out of old lumber. 他们利用旧木料草草地盖起了一间小屋。 4. Among the sawmill customers are the chair factory and other users of cut lumber. 在锯木场的客户中是那些椅子工厂及其他木料用户。 5. He was a lumberjack, living in lumber camps of the American Northwest. 他是个伐木工，住在美国西北的伐木营地里。 6. He refused to lumber himself with a family. 他不愿有家室拖累。', '副词: lumberingly 名词: lumberer 过去式: lumbered 过去分词: lumbered 现在分词: lumbering 第三人称单数: lumbers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('probability', '[ˌprɑːbə\'bɪləti]', 'n.可能性；【数】或然率；机率；【统计】概率，概率论', '1. The probability that it will rain today is high. 今天下雨的可能性很大。 2. The probability of making a mistake increases when you are tired. 你累的时候犯错误的可能性就会增加。 3. Sometimes, love is a kind of probability. 有时，爱情就是一种或然率。 4. I don\'t know how to calculate probability accurately. 不知道怎样才可以准确的计算出或然率。', '名词复数: probabilities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('want', '[wɑːnt]', 'v.要；想要；通缉 n.缺乏；贫穷；需求品', '1. I want large ones, not small ones. 我要大的, 不要小的。 2. He wants me to go with him. 他希望我同他一起去。 3. What they talked about is what we want to know. 他们谈论什么是我们所想要知道的事。 4. He is wanted by the police. 警察正通缉他。 5. The plants died from want of water. 这些植物因缺水而死。', '形容词: wantless 名词: wanter 过去式: wanted 过去分词: wanted 现在分词: wanting 第三人称单数: wants');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('supreme', '[suː\'priːm]', 'adj.最高的；至上的；极度的', '1. The general was girded with the supreme power. 将军被授予最高权力。 2. The safety of the people is the supreme law. 人民的安全是最高的法律。 3. Supreme authority resides in the State. 最高权力属于国家。 4. Wisdom is the supreme part of happiness. 智慧是幸福的顶峰。', '副词: supremely 比较级: supremer 最高级: supremest 名词: supremeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fraud', '[frɔːd]', 'n.欺骗；诈欺；骗子', '1. She was put on trial for fraud. 她因涉及诈骗罪而受审。 2. Investigation of fraud was their commission. 调查诈欺舞弊是他们的任务。 3. He told people that he was a serious and well-known musician, but he was actually a fraud. 他告诉人们说他是一个严肃的著名音乐家,实际上却是个骗子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('team', '[tiːm]', 'n.队；组 v.使相配；使合作；结成一队 adj.团队的', '1. John is the spark plug on his rowing team. 约翰是划船队的中坚分子。 2. A cricket team is comprised of eleven players. 一个板球队由11名队员组成。 3. A team of nurses assisted the doctor in performing the operation. 一组护士协助医生施行手术。 4. It\'s hard to team these colours up. 把这些颜色配起来是困难的。 5. Volleyball is a team game. 排球是一项要求全队默契配合的运动。', '过去式: teamed 过去分词: teamed 现在分词: teaming 第三人称单数: teams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('room', '[ruːm]', 'n.房间；空间；机会 v.寄宿；给…提供留宿', '1. I groped for the light switch in the dark room. 我在黑暗的房间里摸索着找电灯开关。 2. He bounced into the room with a springy step. 他以轻快的跑步跳进房间。 3. There is no more room in the computer file. 计算机文件里没有空间了。 4. There is no room for innovation in standards. 在标准化的过程中没有革新的空间。 5. He\'s rooming with my friend Alan. 他住在我的朋友艾伦家里。', '过去式: roomed 过去分词: roomed 现在分词: rooming 第三人称单数: rooms 名词复数: rooms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obscure', '[əb\'skjʊr]', 'adj.难解的；不著名的；微暗的；[语音学]轻音的 v.使 ... 模糊；隐藏；变模糊 n.模糊不清的东西', '1. The rules for the competition are somewhat obscure. 比赛的规则有点让人费解。 2. The reasons why he did it are obscure. 他做那事的理由还不清楚。 3. The report had been published in an obscure German journal. 这个报道刊登在德国一家不著名的报纸上。 4. He set the bed in an obscure corner. 他把床放在一个昏暗的角落。 5. The moon was obscured by clouds. 月亮被云遮住了。 6. Hence things whichhave perplexed you and made the case more obscure have served to enlighten meand to strengthen my conclusions. 因此，那些使你们大惑不解并且使案情更加模糊不清的事物，却会对我有所启发，并且能加强我的论断。', '副词: obscurely 比较级: obscurer 最高级: obscurest 名词: obscureness 过去式: obscured 过去分词: obscured 现在分词: obscuring 第三人称单数: obscures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forbid', '[fər\'bɪd]', 'vt.禁止；阻止；不许', '1. Smoking is forbidden in this office. 这间办公室禁止吸烟。 2. I forbid you to call me late at night. 我禁止你在深夜给我打电话。 3. Lack of time forbids any further discussion at the point. 由于时间不够，现在不能深入讨论这个问题。 4. Lack of space forbids listing the names of all those who contributed. 篇幅所限,不能一一列出所有贡献者的名字。', '名词: forbiddance 过去式: forbade/forbad 过去分词: forbidden/forbid 现在分词: forbidding 第三人称单数: forbids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('complete', '[kəm\'pliːt]', 'adj.完整的；完成的；彻底的 vt.完成；使完美；使圆满；填（表格等）', '1. We\'ll certainly set up a complete modern industrial system. 我们一定要建立一个完整的现代化工业体系。 2. When the experiment is complete, include your findings in a report. 试验完成後,请把结果写入报告。 3. This is a complete failure. 这是一个彻底的失败。 4. Can you complete your task on time? 你们能按时完成工作吗?', '形容词: completive 副词: completely 比较级: completer 最高级: completest 名词: completeness 过去式: completed 过去分词: completed 现在分词: completing 第三人称单数: completes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('first', '[fɜːrst]', 'adj.第一的；最初的 adv.首先；第一 n.最初；(序数词)第一', '1. He was the first to be there. 他是第一个到达那里的。 2. He came too late to see the first part of the show. 他来得太晚了,没赶上看节目的第一部分。 3. First of all she just smiled, then she started to laugh. 最初她只是微笑，後来才放声大笑。 4. No matter it is windy or rainy,he always comes first. 不论刮风还是下雨,他总是第一个来。 5. What were your first impressions of Beijing? 你对北京的最初印象如何？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('raise', '[reɪz]', 'n.上升；增高；高地 vt.升起；举起；饲养；提出；引起；筹集，募集', '1. The percentage of the pay raise equals the increase in prices. 薪水的提高比率和物价的上升一致。 2. He got a raise in monthly wages. 他的月薪增加了。 3. The first thing that we did when we conquered the town was to haul down the enemy\'s flag and raise our own. 我们占领这座城市以后以后所做的第一件事就是降下城里敌人的旗帜，升起我们自己的旗帜。 4. The guesture might come from Rome, when people raise the right hand to show their extolling and respect for the empire. 这一手势有可能来自罗马,那时人们将右臂举起以表示对帝王的称颂或敬意。', '名词: raiser 过去式: raised 过去分词: raised 现在分词: raising 第三人称单数: raises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rude', '[ruːd]', 'adj.粗鲁无礼的；原始的；未加工的；粗糙的；猛烈的', '1. It\'s strange for her to be so rude. 真奇怪，她竟然会如此粗暴无礼。 2. Don\'t be so rude to your parents! 别对你的父母这么没礼貌！ 3. It\'s very rude of her to leave without telling us. 她不向我们打声招呼就走了，这是非常不礼貌的。 4. These rude tribesmen live in the rain forest. 这些原始部落人生活在雨林之中。', '副词: rudely 比较级: ruder 最高级: rudest 名词: rudeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hop', '[hɑːp]', 'v.跳跃；单脚跳 n.跳跃；单脚跳', '1. The children had a competition to see who could hop the fastest. 孩子们举行比赛, 看谁单足跳跃最快。 2. Several frogs were hopping about on the lawn. 有几只青蛙在草地上跳来跳去。 3. When the burglar heard their car he hopped it out of the window. 那窃贼听到他们汽车的声音就从窗口逃走了。 4. The pursuer cleared the fence in one hop. 追捕者一跳越过了栅栏。', '过去式: hopped 过去分词: hopped 现在分词: hopping 第三人称单数: hops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quote', '[kwoʊt]', 'v.引述；报价；举证 n.引用', '1. She asked the reporter not to quote her remarks. 她要求记者不要引述她的话。 2. Please quote your price in terms of pound. 请您报盘时用英镑报价。 3. Can you quote me a recent instance? 你能给我举一个最近的例子吗？ 4. A direct quote was taken from his speech. 直接引用他的演讲。', '名词: quoter 过去式: quoted 过去分词: quoted 现在分词: quoting 第三人称单数: quotes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('honorable', '[\'ɒnərəbəl]', 'adj.光荣的；可敬的；体面的 =honourable(英).', '1. It is honorable to earn a living with your hands. 靠双手劳动来养活自己是光荣的。 2. It\'s not honorable to deceive them. 欺骗他们是不光彩的。 3. His conduct speaks him honorable. 他的行为表明他是可敬的。 4. He was given an honorable burial. 他的葬礼很体面。', '副词: honorably 名词: honorableness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('merchandise', '[\'mɜːrtʃəndaɪs]', 'n.商品；货物 v.推销；销售；经营', '1. Do you know the trade name of this box of merchandise? 你知道这箱商品的商标吗? 2. Among all the merchandise, I was interested in the cotton piece in particular. 在所有商品中，我对棉布特别感兴趣。 3. Their merchandise is of high quality. 他们的货物质量很好。 4. The merchandise is not up to standard. 货物品质未达标准。 5. We merchandise our furniture by advertising in newspapers. 我们在报上登广告推销家具.', '形容词: merchandisable 名词: merchandiser');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('illness', '[\'ɪlnəs]', 'n.病；疾病', '1. His illness diminished his health. 疾病侵蚀了他的健康。 2. He will pull through his illness soon. 他很快就会恢复健康的。 3. Worry and illness had made him prematurely old. 他心事重重、 疾病缠身，落得个未老先衰。 4. A mysterious illness is affecting all the animals. 一种奇怪的疾病正在侵袭所有的动物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pronoun', '[\'prəʊnaʊn]', 'n.代词', '1. Please make a sentence with this pronoun. 请用这个代词造一个句子。 2. He always put the stress on the pronoun. 他总重读代词。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mood', '[muːd]', 'n.心情；情绪；气氛', '1. I\'m not in the mood to disagree with you. 我没有心思跟你争论。 2. I had never seen Ann in such a good mood before. 我从未见过安的心情这么好过。 3. He\'s in one of his moods today. 他今天闹情绪了。 4. The movie accurately reflects the mood of the time. 电影真实地反映了当时的气氛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strange', '[streɪndʒ]', 'adj.奇怪的；陌生的；生疏或不自在的', '1. It seemed strange that she would leave so early. 奇怪的是她竟然走的这么早。 2. He had a strange expression on his face. 他脸上呈现出奇怪的表情。 3. What strange clothes you\'re wearing! 你穿的衣服真特别! 4. He stood in a strange street. 他站在一条陌生的街道上。', '副词: strangely 比较级: stranger 最高级: strangest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ozone', '[\'oʊzoʊn]', 'n.臭氧；新鲜空气', '1. CFCs cause depletion of atmospheric ozone. 氟氯化碳会损耗大气臭氧。 2. Dyes have to be more resistant to ozone. 染料更能抵制臭氧。 3. Just breathe in the ozone on the sea. 吸吸海上的新鲜空气吧。', '形容词: ozonic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hamper', '[\'hæmpər]', 'vt.妨碍；阻止 n.大篮子', '1. Our progress was hampered by the bad weather. 我们前进时受到了恶劣天气的阻碍。 2. Outdated conventions and bad customs hamper the growth of production. 陈规陋习妨碍生产的发展。 3. The heavy rain hampers the flow of traffic. 大雨阻碍了交通运行。 4. There are some apples in a picnic hamper. 在野餐用的大篮子里有许多苹果。', '过去式: hampered 过去分词: hampered 现在分词: hampering 第三人称单数: hampers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('west', '[west]', 'n.西；西方；西部；西方国家 adj.西方的；西部的 adv.向(在)西方', '1. The earth rotates from west to east. 地球从西向东旋转。 2. The sun rises in the east and sets in the west. 太阳从东方升起，在西方落下。 3. I live in the west of the city. 我住在该城市的西部。 4. The West is the granary of this country. 西部是这个国家的粮仓。 5. We learned from the west countries. 我们向西方国家学习。 6. The building faces west. 这座建筑物面朝西。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('paste', '[peɪst]', 'n.面团；浆糊；糊状物；糊 vt.裱糊；粘贴', '1. The boy squeezed paste into a ball . 孩子把面团捏成了球形。 2. We used paste to attach our designs to the poster. 我们用浆糊把我们设计的图案贴在招贴牌上。 3. He beat the mixture up to a paste. 他把混合料搅成糊状。 4. Stir the flour and milk to a stiff paste. 把面粉和牛奶搅成很稠的糊。 5. She pasted the pictures into a scrapbook. 她把图片贴在剪贴簿上。', '过去式: pasted 过去分词: pasted 现在分词: pasting 第三人称单数: pastes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('era', '[\'ɪrə]', 'n.纪元；时代；年代', '1. Concorde inaugurated new era in aeroplane travel. 协和式飞机开创了空中旅行的新纪元。 2. His death marked the end of an era. 他的死标志著一个时代的结束。 3. We are living in the computer era. 我们正生活在计算机时代。 4. It\'s an era of the miniskirt in the seventies. 七十年代是超短裙时代。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('moon', '[muːn]', 'n.月亮；月球 v.闲逛；虚度；露光臀示人', '1. The moon goes round the earth. 月亮绕着地球转。 2. Last night there was a full moon. 昨晚是满月。 3. The moon peeped out from behind the clouds. 月亮从云层中隐现。 4. The spacecraft is in orbit around the moon. 该航天器在绕月球轨道运行。 5. The boys have nothing to do but moon around in the streets . 这些男孩子没什么事可做，只是在街上闲荡。', '过去式: mooned 过去分词: mooned 现在分词: mooning 第三人称单数: moons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cab', '[kæb]', 'n.出租汽车；司机室；驾驶室；轻便马车 vi.乘出租车', '1. Shall we take a cab there and come back by subway? 我们坐出租车去再乘地铁回来好吗？ 2. The cab speeded them into the centre of the city. 出租汽车载着他们迅速驶往市中心。 3. The truck driver ate lunch in the cab. 卡车司机在司机室里吃午餐。 4. Last night he slept in the driver\'s cab. 他昨天晚上在驾驶室里睡了一晚。 5. I decided to cab to work since I was running late. 因为有点晚了，我决定打车去上班。', '过去式: cabbed 过去分词: cabbed 现在分词: cabbing 第三人称单数: cabs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eyebrow', '[\'aɪbraʊ]', 'n.眉毛；[建]窗头线饰', '1. She raised a questioning eyebrow. 她怀疑地挑起了眉毛。 2. Eyebrows and the eyebrow sweat are dissimilar. 眉毛下与眉毛上的汗水是不一样的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('proficiency', '[prə\'fɪʃnsi]', 'n.熟练；精通', '1. He made little proficiency in literary accomplishments. 他在文学方面成就不多。 2. How do you think of your proficiency in written and spoken English? 你认为你的书面英语和口语熟练程度如何? 3. You need some proficiency in book - keeping for this job. 干这项工作你需要在记帐方面熟练。 4. He acquired some proficiency in English. 他精通英语。', '名词复数: proficiencies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strenuous', '[\'strenjuəs]', 'adj.奋发的；费力的；繁重的；积极的', '1. He made strenuous efforts to improve his reading. 他奋发努力提高阅读能力。 2. I\'ll appreciate your strenuous effort to promote the sale in your market on commission basis. 在市场上为我们的产品尽全力促销的话,我将非常感谢您。 3. She made strenuous efforts to tame her anger. 她竭力压制心头怒火。 4. I\'ll appreciate your strenuous effort to promote the sale in your market on commission basis. 在市场上为我们的产品尽全力促销的话,我将非常感谢您。', '副词: strenuously 名词: strenuosity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tutor', '[\'tuːtər]', 'n.家庭教师；导师 v.指导；当家庭教师；当导师', '1. His parents employed a tutor to teach him Greek. 他父母雇佣了一位家庭教师来教他希腊语。 2. My tutor is an accomplished scholar. 我的导师是一位学识渊博的学者。 3. Most parents have no time to tutor their children. 大部分家长没有时间辅导孩子。 4. For extra money, she tutors on weekends. 为了多挣些钱，她在周末当家庭教师。', '过去式: tutored 过去分词: tutored 现在分词: tutoring 第三人称单数: tutors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('develop', '[dɪ\'veləp]', 'v.发展；发育；开发；冲洗(照片)', '1. Modern music was first developed in Italy. 现代音乐最初是在意大利发展起来的。 2. China can\'t develop in isolation from the rest of the world. 中国的发展离不开世界。 3. Plants develop from seeds, but many animals developed from eggs. 植物由种子发育而成,而许多动物由卵子发育而来。 4. Investors agreed to pool their resources to develop the property. 投资者们同意把大家的资源放在一起共同使用,来开发这块地产。', '形容词: developable 过去式: developed 过去分词: developed 现在分词: developing 第三人称单数: develops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('logical', '[\'lɑːdʒɪkl]', 'adj.符合逻辑的；逻辑上的；合理的', '1. Every argument was stated with logical precision. 每一个论点都阐述得精确严密，符合逻辑。 2. You must learn how to construct a logical argument. 你必须学会怎样确立合乎逻辑的论点。 3. My argument follows the rules of logical induction. 我是遵循逻辑归纳的法则进行论证的。 4. The article has a logical composition. 这篇文章布局合理。', '副词: logically 名词: logicality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('let', '[let]', 'v.让；允许；(用于祈使句表建议、请求、命令)让；假设；出租 n.出租；阻碍；(网球等)触网重发', '1. I won\'t let him get away with that excuse. 我不会让他用那种借口蒙混过去。 2. I don\'t agree with all you say, but I\'ll let it go at that. 我并不完全同意你说的话，但我不再多说了。 3. No visitors are let into the committee meetings. 委员会会议不允许任何访问者闯入。 4. Let me have a look at this watch. 把这只表让我看看。 5. I can\'t get a let for my house. 我的房子租不出去。', '过去式: let 过去分词: let 现在分词: letting 第三人称单数: lets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('police', '[pə\'liːs]', 'n.警察；警方 v.维持治安；管辖；监督', '1. The police have caught the murderer. 警察已经抓获杀人凶手。 2. His strange behavior made the police suspicious. 他不寻常的举止引起了警察的怀疑。 3. It\'s the duty of the police to preserve the public order. 维护公共秩序是警察的职责。 4. The police are always hounding me. 警方一直在追捕我。 5. United Nation forces are sent to police the troubled area. 联合国部队被派去维持该动乱地区的秩序。', '形容词: policeable 名词: policer 名词复数: police 过去式: policed 过去分词: policed 现在分词: policing 第三人称单数: polices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plumber', '[\'plʌmər]', 'n.管道工', '1. He is an apprentice plumber. 他是个见习水管工人。 2. The plumber went down to the cellar to fix the leaky pipe. 管道工到地下室去修漏水的管子。 3. We had to call a plumber to unblock the drains. 我们得叫管道工来通一通下水道。 4. The plumber stowed all his gear in a canvas bag. 管子工把他所有的工具都装进一只帆布袋里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('airline', '[\'erlaɪn]', 'n.航线；航空公司', '1. Beijing to Guangzhou is a daily airline of CAAC. 北京到广州是中国民航每天的定期航线。 2. The airline company launched a European route for the first time. 这个航空公司首度放飞欧洲航线。 3. The airline has checked his luggage out. 航空公司已把他的行李运走了。 4. Take an airline as an illustration. 以航空公司为例。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('award', '[ə\'wɔːrd]', 'n.奖品；奖 v.授予；给予；判给', '1. It is impossible to honor her with the award. 奖品授给她是不可能的。 2. The child smiled at his teacher as he received the award. 孩子接过奖品时朝老师微笑着。 3. It is the highest award a producer can receive. 这是一个制作人所能获得的最高奖项。 4. Bill accepted the championship award on behalf of the team. 比尔代表他的队接受了冠军奖。 5. The university awarded him an honorary degree. 这所大学授给他名誉学位。', '形容词: awardable 名词: awarder 过去式: awarded 过去分词: awarded 现在分词: awarding 第三人称单数: awards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('missile', '[\'mɪsl]', 'n.导弹；投射物', '1. The missile deflected from its trajectory. 导弹已偏离轨道。 2. The smallest deflection of the missile could bring disaster. 导弹有极微小的偏斜也可能酿出大祸。 3. The missile had blown the battleship asunder. 炮弹把战舰炸碎了。 4. A missile was projected into space. 导弹被发射升空。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tempo', '[\'tempoʊ]', 'n.拍子；节奏；速率', '1. We play the music of Mozart at the slow tempo. 我们以慢速演奏了莫扎特的音乐。 2. Don\'t let the other team dictate the tempo of the game. 别让对方球队控制比赛的节奏。 3. We should keep pace with the swift tempo of the day. 我们应跟上时代的飞速步伐。 4. All this was comparatively slow until, with the coming of science, the tempo was suddenly raised. 所有这些发展都比较缓慢，直到出现了科学，其速度才突然加快。', '名词复数: tempos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remote', '[rɪ\'moʊt]', 'adj.遥远的；偏僻的；远程的；(感情等)距离很大 n.远程操作', '1. The most remote two points in this world are two estranged hearts. 人世间相距最远的两点,是两颗隔膜的心。 2. This is a village remote from the madding crowd. 这是一个远离喧嚣尘世的村庄。 3. Mail comes to this remote village only once a week. 邮车每周只到这个偏僻的村庄一次。 4. The bomb was exploded by remote control. 这颗炸弹是遥控引爆的。 5. Actuation is often desired for process automation, precision timing, and remote operation not possible with manual valves alone. 执行机构经常用于实现紧靠手动阀门无法实现的工艺过程的自动化，准确定时，以及远程操作。', '副词: remotely 比较级: remoter 最高级: remotest 名词: remoteness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dynasty', '[\'daɪnəsti]', 'n.朝代；王朝', '1. How many dynasties are there in China\'s history? 中国历史上有多少个朝代？ 2. The Qing Dynasty ended in 1911. 清朝结束于1911年。 3. The Tang Dynasty is a period remarkable for its liberality. 唐朝是一段以开明著称的时期。 4. He was the son of a fallen dynasty. 他是一个没落王朝的后代。', '形容词: dynastic 副词: dynastically 名词复数: dynasties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('image', '[\'ɪmɪdʒ]', 'n.印象；形象；影像；图像；肖像 vt.反映；想像；描绘', '1. We have an image of the U.S. as a very rich country. 我们印象中的美国是个富国。 2. How can we improve our image? 我们该怎样来改善自己的形象呢？ 3. Her image rose before him. 她的影像在他眼前浮现。 4. You can add an Image control to display an image. 您可以添加Image控件来显示图像。 5. The image in the mirror reflects his mood. 镜子里映出的影像反映出了他的心情。', '形容词: imageless 过去式: imaged 过去分词: imaged 现在分词: imaging 第三人称单数: images');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('testify', '[\'testɪfaɪ]', 'v.作证；证明；声明', '1. He testified that he had not seen the accident. 他作证说他没有看见那次事故。 2. He agreed to testify on behalf of the accused man. 他同意为被告作证。 3. Her actions testify to her good character. 她的行为证明了她的人品是好的。 4. All kinds of human experience testify to the close link between love and fear. 人类的种种经验都证明了爱与怕之间的紧密联系。', '名词: testification 过去式: testified 过去分词: testified 现在分词: testifying 第三人称单数: testifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('panic', '[\'pænɪk]', 'n.惊慌；恐慌 v.使…惊慌；感到恐慌 adj.恐慌的；惊慌的', '1. There was a panic when the building caught fire. 大楼起火时, 人们一片惊慌。 2. Rumours of an imminent earthquake startled a panic. 谣传即将发生地震引起了一阵恐慌。 3. The thunder panicked the horse. 雷声使马受惊了。 4. The idea might panic the investors. 这个想法可能会使投资者惶恐不安。 5. The financial crisis caused panic selling of securities. 金融危机引发了恐慌之下的债权抛售。', '形容词: panicky 过去式: panicked 过去分词: panicked 现在分词: panicking 第三人称单数: panics');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rhythm', '[\'rɪðəm]', 'n.节奏；节律；（事件或过程）有规律的反复出现', '1. The song has a syncopated rhythm in the jazz version. 这首歌曲改编为爵士乐後采用了切分音节奏。 2. Stress and rhythm are important in speaking English. 说英语时，重音和节奏是很重要的。 3. He is trying to play the same tune in a different rhythm. 他正试图用不同节奏演奏同一个曲子。 4. The rhythm of her heart beating is normal. 她的心跳节律是正常的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gain', '[ɡeɪn]', 'n.获得；收益；增益 v.获得；到达；增加；获利；(钟、表等)走得快', '1. No pain, no gain. 不劳则无获。 2. He has no aspiration for fame or gain. 他不图名利。 3. It is not for the love of gain that he does so. 他这样做并非为了得什么好处。 4. You will gain experience if nothing more in that job. 如果这个工作没什么突出的,你至少可以获得经验。', '过去式: gained 过去分词: gained 现在分词: gaining 第三人称单数: gains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lag', '[læɡ]', 'v.落后；减退；缓慢进行 n.落后；时间间隔', '1. Some of the runners in the race began to lag. 参加比赛的运动员中有一些开始落後了。 2. The children always lag behind when we go for a walk. 我们出去散步时，孩子们总是落在后面。 3. Interest lags in such matters. 对这类事情的兴趣慢慢减少了。 4. It takes a lot of time to catch up with a cultural lag. 文化的落后需要长时间才能赶上。', '名词: lagger 过去式: lagged 过去分词: lagged 现在分词: lagging 第三人称单数: lags');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('factory', '[\'fæktri]', 'n.工厂；制造厂', '1. I got a job in a textile factory. 我在一家纺织厂找到一份工作。 2. The company wished to locate its new factory beside the river. 这家公司希望把新工厂建在河边。 3. The car factory is situated on the edge of the town. 这座汽车制造厂坐落在该城的边上。 4. He works on the assemblylineat the shoe factory. 他在制鞋厂装配线上工作。', '名词复数: factories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nylon', '[\'naɪlɑːn]', 'n.【U】尼龙 （复数）nylons：女长袜.', '1. This coat is made of nylon. 这件衣服是尼龙的。 2. She strung the beads with a fine nylon. 她用细尼龙线把珠子串了起来。 3. Cotton is more comfortable to wear than nylon. 棉布比尼龙穿着舒服。 4. Most females love wearing dresses with nylons. 大多数女性喜欢穿裙配长袜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('happen', '[\'hæpən]', 'vi.发生；碰巧；出现；偶遇', '1. The accident happened at six o\'clock. 事故发生在六点钟。 2. It is impossible to anticipate when it will happen. 不可能预料这事何时发生。 3. I happened to see her yesterday. 我昨天碰巧见到她。 4. I happen to have the official statistics with me. 我碰巧身边有官方的统计数字。', '过去式: happened 过去分词: happened 现在分词: happening 第三人称单数: happens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shift', '[ʃɪft]', 'v.移动；改变；换挡；字型转换 n.轮班；变化；移动；计谋；轮班职工', '1. The tools shift around in the car boot every time we turn a corner. 我们每次转弯，汽车行李箱里的工具就来回动。 2. The Left is shifting their ground. 左派正在改变立场。 3. You have to shift as you drive around the corner. 你拐角时要换挡变速。 4. They were taking turns to be on the night shift. 他们轮流做夜班。', '名词: shifter 过去式: shifted 过去分词: shifted 现在分词: shifting 第三人称单数: shifts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('envelope', '[\'ɑnvəˌloʊp]', 'n.信封；壳层；封袋', '1. There are several enclosures in the envelope. 信封内装有几份附件。 2. I use a prepaid envelope. 我用了一个邮资已付的信封。 3. He glued a stamp onto the envelope. 他把邮票贴在信封上。 4. The surface of the sun is a glowing gas envelope. 太阳的表面是一层炽热的气体层。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diagnose', '[ˌdaɪəɡ\'noʊs]', 'v.判断；诊断(疾病)', '1. Geological investigations must correctly diagnose a specific soil-like condition. 地质调查必须正确地判断出明确的土状条件。 2. What more will you want to know to diagnose this problem? 要弄清这个问题，你还需要知道些什么? 3. The book diagnoses our present economic ills. 这本书切中了我们现在经济的时弊。 4. The test is used to diagnose a variety of diseases. 此项化验可用于诊断多种疾病。', '形容词: diagnosable 过去式: diagnosed 过去分词: diagnosed 现在分词: diagnosing 第三人称单数: diagnoses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dialog', '[\'daɪəˌlɒg]', 'n.对话；对白 =dialogue<英>', '1. At last there can be a reasonable dialog between our two governments. 我们两国最后终于能理智地进行对话了。 2. The writer is not very good at writing dialogs. 这个作家不太擅长写对白。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('patent', '[\'pætnt]', 'n.专利；特许 vt.给予专利权 adj.专利的；显著的', '1. The patent runs out in three years time. 这项专利期限为3年。 2. He got a patent for this invention. 他获得了这项发明的专利权。 3. The government patented the device to its inventor. 政府给予发明者专利权。 4. This is a packet of a patent cement mix. 这是一包专利水泥混合料。', '形容词: patentable 名词: patentability 过去式: patented 过去分词: patented 现在分词: patenting 第三人称单数: patents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('retire', '[rɪ\'taɪər]', 'v.退休；撤退；离去；就寝；主动退出比赛；收回（货币）；赎回（票据） n.退休，退职', '1. My father retired at the age of 60. 我父亲六十岁时退休了。 2. The old worker decided to retire to the country. 那们老工人决定退休后搬到乡下去。 3. Our forces retired to prepared positions. 我们的部队撤退到既设阵地上。 4. After lunch he retired to his study. 他午饭后就到书房去了。', '过去式: retired 过去分词: retired 现在分词: retiring 第三人称单数: retires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flourish', '[\'flɜːrɪʃ]', 'v.茂盛；繁荣；挥舞；活跃 n.挥舞；花样；炫耀；华丽词藻', '1. There were two or three palm trees flourishing in the promenade garden. 街心花园里有两三棵枝繁叶茂的棕榈树。 2. Plants will not flourish without water. 没有水植物就不会长得茂盛。 3. These plants flourish in a damp climate. 这些植物在潮湿的气候下长势茂盛。 4. Our business seemed to flourish. 我们在生意看上去很兴隆。 5. She rode by with a flourish of her whip. 她骑马挥鞭而过。', '名词: flourisher 过去式: flourished 过去分词: flourished 现在分词: flourishing 第三人称单数: flourishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('before', '[bɪ\'fɔːr]', 'conj.在 ... 以前 pref.在 ... 以前；在..前面 adv.以前；以往；之前', '1. B comes before C in the alphabet. B在字母表里排在C之前。 2. He made a statement before the House of Commons. 他在下议院当众发表了一个声明。 3. He always put the interests of others before his own. 他总把他人的利益放在第一位。 4. I\'d met him once before. 我曾经见过他。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rescue', '[\'reskjuː]', 'vt.营救；援救 n.营救；救援', '1. He dived from the bridge to rescue the drowning child. 他从桥上跳入水中去抢救那溺水儿童。 2. Had Jim not dived in to rescue him, the boy would have drowned. 如果不是吉姆跳下水去救，那小孩早就淹死了。 3. The government has rescued the firm from bankruptcy by giving them a grant. 政府拨款给这家公司使其免于破产。 4. The rescue attempt was impeded by bad weather. 营救工作受到恶劣天气的妨碍。', '形容词: rescuable 名词: rescuer 过去式: rescued 过去分词: rescued 现在分词: rescuing 第三人称单数: rescues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('boom', '[buːm]', 'n.繁荣；兴旺；激增；低沉声 n.帆杠；吊杆；支臂；尾桁；水栅 vi.急速增长；发出低沉声 vt.使兴旺；促进', '1. It\'s a boom year this year. 今年是繁荣昌盛的一年。 2. He made his pile during the property boom. 在房地产生意兴隆期间他发了大财。 3. The oil market is enjoying a boom. 石油市场欣欣向荣。 4. City growth far outran the general population boom. 城市的发展大大超过总的人口激增。 5. The boom swung over the deck. 帆杠在甲板上转动。 6. Business is booming. 商业正日趋繁荣。 7. Foreign investments boomed the city. 国外投资使这个城市迅速繁荣起来。', '过去式: boomed 过去分词: boomed 现在分词: booming 第三人称单数: booms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('more', '[mɔːr]', 'pron.更多的；另外的；更大的 adv.更多；再；另外；进一步', '1. There are more cars on the road in the summer than in the winter. 夏天路上的车子比冬天多。 2. We need two more pairs of bath slippers. 我们另外再要两双洗澡用拖鞋。 3. They are proud of taking more power. 他们以掌握更大的权力为荣。 4. As a freelancer, he has more free time to himself. 因为是个自由职业者,他有更多属于自己的自由时间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nitrogen', '[\'naɪtrədʒən]', 'n.氮', '1. Air consists chiefly of nitrogen. 空气主要由氮气组成。 2. The lamp is full of gaseous nitrogen. 灯里充满了气体氮。 3. Nitrogen is a gas without colour or smell. 氮是一种无色无臭的气体。 4. Nitrogen forms most of the Earth\'s air. 地球上空气的大部分成分是氮气。', '形容词: nitrogenous 简写符号: N');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coast', '[koʊst]', 'n.海岸；海滨', '1. Spray slaps the coast ceaselessly. 海浪不停地拍打着海岸。 2. Fishing boats were anchored all along the coast. 渔船沿着岸抛锚停泊。 3. He is going to live by the coast for the sake of his health. 他为了自己的健康，打算到海滨地区去居住。 4. We spent a week exploring the coast. 我们花了一周时间在海滨进行探测。', '形容词: coastal 过去式: coasted 过去分词: coasted 现在分词: coasting 第三人称单数: coasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('undoubtedly', '[ʌn\'daʊtɪdli]', 'adv.无疑地', '1. Undoubtedly Hitler will fight the great powers. 无疑地要接着希特勒同各大国打。 2. Carlson\'s feeling for people undoubtedly helped him maintain his brand of teamwork. 卡尔森对人的感情无疑地帮助保住了他那协同工作的牌子。', '形容词: undoubted');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sincere', '[sɪn\'sɪr]', 'adj.真诚的；诚挚的', '1. How can I persuade you that I am sincere? 怎样才能使你相信我是真心实意的呢? 2. I will oblige any sincere request. 我会答应任何诚意的请求。 3. I think he is sincere and quite without affectation. 我认为他为人诚挚，毫不做作。 4. Sincere congratulations on your son wedding please convey our best wish. 令郎喜结良缘谨此致以诚挚的祝贺并请转达最美好的祝愿。', '副词: sincerely 比较级: sincerer 最高级: sincerest 名词: sincereness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('standpoint', '[\'stændpɔɪnt]', 'n.立场；观点', '1. This is far away from the viewer\'s standpoint. 这是远离观众的立场。 2. We only look at things based on a certain standpoint. 我们所有的人只是站在某一立场来看待事物。 3. Let\'s look at this from a historical standpoint. 让我们从历史的观点来看待这一切。 4. Don\'t foist your standpoint on me. 不要把你的观点强加于我。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('call', '[kɔːl]', 'vt.呼叫；打电话；把 ...称为 n.打电话；访问；召唤；呼叫；把 ... 看作 vi.呼叫；(短暂的)拜访', '1. The shouting boy did not hear his mother call him. 大声叫嚷的孩子听不到妈妈的叫唤。 2. I\'ll call you if you give me a name card. 给我一张名片吧,我会打电话给你。 3. Most people call me Bob. How do I address you? 大家叫我鲍勃,我怎么称呼你? 4. Shortly after we arrived at that hotel, we made a call back home. 我们到达旅馆不久,就马上打电话回家。 5. She called to her father for help. 她向她父亲喊叫求救。', '过去式: called 过去分词: called 现在分词: calling 第三人称单数: calls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('daylight', '[\'deɪlaɪt]', 'n.日光；白昼；黎明', '1. I\'d prefer to walk home in daylight. 我比较喜欢在日光里步行回家。 2. One of their big weaknesses is daylight. 他们其中一个大弱点是日光！ 3. Daylight robberies were of frequent occurrence. 白昼行窃已司空见惯了。 4. A diurnal animal hunts its food during daylight. 白天活动的动物在白昼时猎食。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('youngster', '[\'jʌŋstər]', 'n.年青人；少年；小伙子；儿童；幼小动物', '1. Why is the youngster\'s trouble very much? 为什么年青人的烦恼很多？ 2. The youngster always has solitary longing. 年青人总有独居的渴望。 3. A poor old man was once a lazy youngster. 一个懒惰的少年将来就是一个褴褛的老人。 4. Looking up to Li as a youngster, Wang also dreams of becoming a great hero one day. 仰望李作为少年，王还梦想成为一个伟大的英雄一天。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('insect', '[\'ɪnsekt]', 'n.昆虫；虫子；卑微的人', '1. The insect bit him and drew blood from his arm. 那只昆虫叮在他的手臂上吸血。 2. A cocoon is a kind of silk covering made by an insect. 蚕茧是由昆虫制造的一种由丝组成的外包层。 3. She stamped on the insect and killed it. 她踩死了一只虫子。 4. A locust is a kind of destructive insect. 蝗虫是一种害虫。', '形容词: insectival 名词复数: insects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spare', '[sper]', 'adj.备用的；多余的；闲置的 v.抽出；饶恕；赦免；节约 n.备用品；剩余', '1. Do you have a spare tire? 你有备用轮胎吗? 2. Please stay with us. We have a spare room for you. 请住下吧,我们有给你的备用房间。 3. What do you like doing in your spare time? 你在闲暇时喜欢做什么？ 4. Can you bear me a hand tomorrow?I want to rearrange some things in our spare room. 明天你能帮个忙吗?我想把我家闲置着的那个房间里的一些东西新整理安排一下。 5. Can you spare me five minutes? 你能抽出五分钟和我谈谈吗？ 6. I\'ve lost my key and I haven\'t got a spare. 我把钥匙丢了，还没有备用的。', '副词: sparely 比较级: sparer 最高级: sparest 名词: spareness 过去式: spared 过去分词: spared 现在分词: sparing 第三人称单数: spares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('multiply', '[\'mʌltɪplaɪ]', 'vt.乘；增加 vi.做乘法；繁衍 adv.多样地；多重地', '1. If you multiply four by five, the answer is twenty. 四乘以五,答案是二十。 2. Let us multiply the height by the width to determine the area. 用宽乘以高来确定面积。 3. This will multiply our chances of success. 这将增加我们成功的机会。 4. He managed to multiply his profits. 他成功地增加了利润。 5. He learned to multiply at the age of five. 他五岁学会做乘法。', '过去式: multiplied 过去分词: multiplied 现在分词: multiplying 第三人称单数: multiplies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('professor', '[prə\'fesər]', 'n.教授；老师', '1. Our professor is a man of profound learning. 我们的教授是一个学识渊博的人。 2. The professor invited his students to his home for conversation. 教授邀请学生们到自己家里会晤。 3. Professor Green, lately of Princeton, is now head of the department at California. 格林教授不久前在普林斯顿任教，现在是加州大学的系主任。 4. I\'d like you to meet my geography professor. 我想介绍我的地理老师给你认识。', '形容词: professorial 副词: professorially 名词: professorship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('balloon', '[bə\'luːn]', 'n.气球；球状物 vt.使膨胀 vi.乘气球飞行；激增；如气球般膨胀 adj.气球状的', '1. A balloon floated across the sky. 有个气球从空中飘过。 2. He balloons his cheeks when he is hesitant. 他迟疑不决时会鼓起双颊。 3. He tried to balloon around the earth but storms forced him to land in China. 他试图乘气球做环球旅行，但风暴迫使他降落在中国。 4. Our expenses had ballooned. 我们的开销大大增加了。', '名词: balloonist 过去式: ballooned 过去分词: ballooned 现在分词: ballooning 第三人称单数: balloons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('balcony', '[\'bælkəni]', 'n.阳台；楼座；包厢', '1. The prospect from the balcony was breathtaking. 从阳台上看去景色美极了。 2. He planted some flowers on the balcony that projects over the street. 他在那个伸出到街上的阳台上种了些花。 3. He was watching a performance from the balcony. 他正在从楼厅上看电影。 4. I\'m sorry, all the balcony seats are sold out. 抱歉,包厢的票都卖完了。', '名词复数: balconies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stir', '[stɜːr]', 'vt.激起；惹起；搅和 vi.活动；引起；挪动 n.骚乱；感动(激动；愤怒或震动)；搅拌', '1. The story stirred her sympathy. 这故事激起了她的同情心。 2. They tried to stir the peoples of the world into triumphant action. 他们试图激励人民大众的无限热情。 3. The oatmeal lumps if you don\'t stir it well. 如果你不好好搅拌，麦片粥会结块。 4. He didn\'t stir while sitting there. 他坐在那里一动不动。 5. The news caused quite a stir in the village. 那消息在村里引起了一片混乱。', '名词: stirrer 过去式: stirred 过去分词: stirred 现在分词: stirring 第三人称单数: stirs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('persecute', '[\'pɜːrsɪkjuːt]', 'vt.迫害；烦扰；为难', '1. They persecute those who do not conform to their idea. 他们迫害那些不信奉他们思想的人。 2. They came to America after being persecuted for their religious beliefs. 他们是在他们因宗教信仰而受到迫害之后来到美洲的。 3. Once the affair became public, he was persecuted by the press. 事情公开後，他便受到新闻界的纠缠。 4. He persecuted me with various delicate questions. 他用种种微妙的问题把我难倒了。', '形容词: persecutive 名词: persecutee 过去式: persecuted 过去分词: persecuted 现在分词: persecuting 第三人称单数: persecutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elephant', '[\'elɪfənt]', 'n.大象；庞大笨拙难处理的事物', '1. The elephant smashed through the trees. 大象在树林中横冲直撞。 2. He said he could eat an elephant to appease his hunger. 他说他吃光一头大象才能充饥。 3. Jan\'s factory is an absolute white elephant. 简的那个工厂成了一个大包袱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flame', '[fleɪm]', 'n.火焰；热情；燃烧；情人 v.燃烧；爆发；面红', '1. The candle flame flickered and went out. 烛火摇曳着，随即熄灭了。 2. Billows of flame swept through the forest. 熊熊烈火席卷森林。 3. He and I were kindled by a great flame of patriotism. 我和他由于一股爱国主义的热情都激动起来了。 4. It\'s been dry for so long that the forest could burst into flame at any moment. 天气干燥了这么久，森林随时都会燃烧起来。 5. The evening sky flamed with red and orange. 傍晚天空的颜色是一片火红和橘黄相间。', '名词: flamer 过去式: flamed 过去分词: flamed 现在分词: flaming 第三人称单数: flames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('convey', '[kən\'veɪ]', 'vt.表达；传达；运输；转移', '1. I find it hard to convey my feelings in word. 我觉得难以用言语表达我的感情。 2. Word will suffice to convey his grief. 他的悲伤足以用言辞表达。 3. A vibrating membrane in the ear helps to convey sounds to the brain. 耳膜的振动帮助声音传送到大脑。 4. This train conveys both passengers and goods. 这趟列车客货均载。', '形容词: conveyable 过去式: conveyed 过去分词: conveyed 现在分词: conveying 第三人称单数: conveys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heroin', '[\'heroʊɪn]', 'n.海洛因', '1. Heroin is a killer. 海洛因是致命的毒品。 2. She was arrested for pushing heroin. 她因贩卖海洛因而被捕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('home', '[hoʊm]', 'n.家；家庭；收容所；栖息地；发源地 adv.在家；回家；在国内；回国；正中目标 adj.家用的；国内的；总部的；（比赛）主场的 v.提供住处；朝向', '1. She lives a long way from home. 她远远地离开故乡在外地生活。 2. My home isn\'t very big, but very comfortable. 我家不很大，但很舒适。 3. He is planning to establish a home. 他正计划建立家庭。 4. The aged is taken care of in the old folks home. 老年人在养老院里受到照顾。 5. Is he home from work? 他下班回家了吗？ 6. This is my home phone number. 这是我家的电话号码。 7. Someone will home you when you arrive there. 你到那儿后，有人会给你安排住处的。', '过去式: homed 过去分词: homed 现在分词: homing 第三人称单数: homes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fearful', '[\'fɪrfl]', 'adj.担心的；可怕的；<口>非常的', '1. They were fearful that the river would flood. 他们担心河流会发洪水。 2. A fearful person is a weak person. 怕这怕那的人是软弱的人。 3. I have ever witnessed a fearful accident. 我曾目睹一场可怕的事故。', '副词: fearfully 名词: fearfulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('music', '[\'mjuːzɪk]', 'n.音乐；美妙的声音；乐谱', '1. He is interested in music. 他对音乐有兴趣。 2. Listening to the music has a calming influence on her. 听音乐对她起了一种镇静的作用。 3. I was enchanted with the sweet music. 这美妙的音乐使我心醉。 4. He listened with pleasure to the beautiful music. 他陶醉在美妙的音乐中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pendulum', '[\'pendʒələm]', 'n.摆锤；钟摆；摇摆不定', '1. A pendulum oscillates. 摆锤能摆动。 2. The pendulum of the clock in my room is a bear. 我房间的钟摆是小熊形状的。 3. The pendulum swings with great regularity. 钟摆很有规律地摆动着。 4. Since the last election, the pendulum of public opinion has swung back against the government. 自从上次大选以来,公众舆论又转回到反对政府。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('distinction', '[dɪ\'stɪŋkʃn]', 'n.荣誉；差别；优秀；对比；区分', '1. These are the highest distinctions that have ever been given by our government. 这些是我国政府迄今授予的最高荣誉称号。 2. Keller received many awards of great distinction. 凯勒被授予很多殊荣奖。 3. He had the distinction of being the first man to walk on the moon. 他以月球上第一个行走而闻名于世。 4. There is a fine distinction between the two words. 这两个字之间有细微区别。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fruit', '[fruːt]', 'n.果实；成果；水果 v.结果实', '1. The bough was loaded with fruit. 树枝上果实累累。 2. The flower becomes fruit when it worships. 花崇拜时便成了果实。 3. Their research project haven\' t borne fruit. 他们的研究课题还未取得成果。 4. The book is the fruit of years of research. 这本书是多年研究的成果。 5. The apple trees are fruiting early this year. 今年苹果树很早结果。', '名词复数: fruit 过去式: fruited 过去分词: fruited 现在分词: fruiting 第三人称单数: fruits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tail', '[teɪl]', 'n.后部；尾巴；尾部；辫子；跟随者 (复）tails: 燕尾服；(硬币的)反面 vt.跟踪；盯 ... 的梢；为 ... 装尾巴 vi.尾随；附于其后；逐渐减少', '1. He drove into the back of my truck and smashed the tail light. 他开车撞进我卡车的后部，把我的尾灯撞得粉碎。 2. Lizards have four legs and a long tail. 蜥蜴有四条腿和一条长尾巴。 3. The sting of a scorpion is in its tail. 蝎子的毒钩在其尾部。 4. She braids her hair in little tails. 她把头发编成一根根小辫。 5. A coin has two sides,a head and a tail. 硬币有正反两面。 6. I have notified them to watch and tail him. 我已通知了他们监视跟踪他。 7. The children tailed after the parade. 孩子们跟在游行队伍后面。', '形容词: tailless 过去式: tailed 过去分词: tailed 现在分词: tailing 第三人称单数: tails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('booth', '[buːθ]', 'n.货摊；电话亭；小间', '1. Would you please watch over my booth? 请您照料一下我的摊位好吗? 2. I\'ll give him a call from the phone booth on the corner. 我到街角的电话亭给他打个电话。 3. It happened that there was a telephone booth nearby. 碰巧在附近有个公用电话亭。 4. They sat in a corner booth, away from other diners. 他们坐在餐厅角落的小隔间里，与别的就餐者分开。', '名词复数: booths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expel', '[ɪk\'spel]', 'vt.驱逐；开除；排出', '1. Russia has lately decided to expel a US diplomat from its land, . 俄国最近驱逐了一名美国外交官。 2. He was expelled from the school. 他被学校开除了。 3. The headmaster decided to make an example of the pupil and expel him from the school. 校长决定开除该生以儆效尤。 4. The lungs expel carbon dioxide when we exhale. 当我们呼气时,肺所排出来的是二氧化碳。', '形容词: expellable 名词: expeller 过去式: expelled 过去分词: expelled 现在分词: expelling 第三人称单数: expels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('handkerchief', '[\'hæŋkərtʃɪf]', 'n.手帕；方巾；围巾', '1. She was playing with her handkerchief all the while during the speech. 她在演讲时一直都在玩弄手帕。 2. I polished my buttons with a handkerchief. 我用手帕把钮扣擦亮。 3. She embroidered her initials on the handkerchief. 她把她姓名的起首字母绣在手帕上。 4. I folded the handkerchief and put it in my pocket. 我折好手绢，放进口袋里。', '名词复数: handkerchiefs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('watt', '[wɑːt]', 'n.瓦特', '1. The lamp needs a 100-watt bulb. 那盏灯需要100瓦的灯泡。 2. By last year the price had fallen to about $2.70 per watt. 到去年为止，这个价格已经下跌到了2.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('production', '[prə\'dʌkʃn]', 'n.生产；产量；作品；成果；分泌；制作；上映；播出', '1. We must increase production levels. 我们必须提高生产水平。 2. The necessary outcome of a war is a fall in production. 战争带来的必然结果就是生产力下降。 3. If we cannot sell more goods, we\'ll have to cut back on the production. 如果我们不能卖出更多的货物,就必须降低产量。 4. This book on education is his latest production. 这本论述教育的书是他的最新作品。', '形容词: productional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pension', '[\'penʃn]', 'n.养老金；退休金；抚恤金；年金；（欧洲等地的）私人小旅店 v.发退休金', '1. He\'s got nothing beyond his state pension. 除了国家发的养老金，他一无所有。 2. He went to the post office to draw his pension. 他到邮局去取退休金了。 3. concede one\'s attention 4. He had stayed at the pension for a fortnight. 他已在那个小旅馆待了两个星期。 5. He was pensioned off and replaced with a younger man. 他被迫退休，由一年轻人接替其职务。', '形容词: pensionable 过去式: pensioned 过去分词: pensioned 现在分词: pensioning 第三人称单数: pensions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dental', '[\'dentl]', 'adj.牙齿的；牙科的', '1. All these rise to protect action to dental enamel. 所有这些都对牙齿的珐琅质起到保护作用。 2. Dental care can prevent early tooth loss and bladder or kidney infections. 牙齿的护理可以防止过早掉牙和膀光或肾感染。 3. Further evidence-based investigation with regards to neonatal and dental fields is needed. 舌系带黏连的诊断与治疗须要更多新生儿科与小儿牙科的调查研究，期盼能给父母亲们客观的建议。 4. Generally, traditional behavior management skill will be effective and efficient used for dental care in pediatric dentistry. 摘要基本上，儿童牙科的治疗，都尽量以常规的行为处理技巧来照顾病人即可。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('combination', '[ˌkɑːmbɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.结合；结合到一起的事物或人；密码', '1. It is the combination of wit and political analysis that makes his articles so readable. 他的生花妙笔与政治分析相得益彰，使他的文章脍炙人口。 2. The firm is working on a new product in combination with several overseas partners. 公司正在联合几家海外合伙人制造新产品。 3. A combination of factors led to her decision to resign. 综合各种因素之後她决定辞职。 4. If you want to open the lock, you must know the combination. 如果你想要打开这把锁,你必须知道密码。', '形容词: combinational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clinic', '[\'klɪnɪk]', 'n.诊所；门诊部；科室', '1. His clinic is near the newly-built railway station. 他的诊所在新建的火车站附近。 2. He is being treated at a private clinic. 他正在私人诊所接受治疗。 3. He will be tested for HIV at the hospital clinic. 他将在医院门诊部接受艾滋病检查。 4. She is attending the antenatal clinic. 她正接受产前检查.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lateral', '[\'lætərəl]', 'adj.侧面的；横向的；旁边的 n.侧面；[语]侧音 vi.完成横向穿越', '1. The slight keel and lateral rail design provide directional stability and excellent tracking. 船身轻微倾起及侧面的扶手设计均有助转向及航行时高稳定性。 2. For the lateral movement of solids we again need to specify a mechanism. 对固体颗粒的横向运动，我们还需提出一种机制。 3. set fire to sth 4. Lateral renal malrotation is relatively uncommon. 摘要侧面肾脏异常旋转是相当少见。', '副词: laterally 过去式: lateraled/lateralled 过去分词: lateraled/lateralled 现在分词: lateraling/lateralling 第三人称单数: laterals/laterals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('affluent', '[\'æfluənt]', 'adj.富裕的 n.支流', '1. We live in an affluent society . 我们生活在一个富裕的社会中。 2. He was born to an affluent family. 他生在富裕人家。 3. A car and a house are considered as necessities in an affluent society. 在一个富裕的社会里,汽车和洋房都被当作是必需品。', '副词: affluently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('undermine', '[ˌʌndər\'maɪn]', 'vt.逐渐削弱；暗中损害；在...下挖；从根基处损害', '1. They will do anything to undermine their adversary\'s reputation. 他们会不择手段地去损害对手的名誉。 2. The President\'s enemies are spreading rumours to undermine his authority. 总统的敌人在散布谣言以逐渐破坏他的威信。 3. Badgers had undermined the foundations of the church. 獾在这座教堂的地基处打了洞。 4. A mole can undermine the strongest rampart. 一只田鼠能毁坏最坚固的堡垒。', '过去式: undermined 过去分词: undermined 现在分词: undermining 第三人称单数: undermines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fixture', '[\'fɪkstʃər]', 'n.固定物；固定装置；固定成员；【机】夹具', '1. A new fireplace fixture was fixed in the wall. 新的壁炉的固定物被固定在墙上。 2. In America, this kind of computers have become a fixture in offices. 这种电子计算机现在已成为美国各地办公室里的必备之物。 3. The flagpole has been a fixture since the building was first opened a century ago. 这个旗杆从一个世纪前饭店开业起就一直固定在那里。 4. The price includes all fixtures and fittings. 这个价钱把全部固定装置和设备都打在里面了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('badly', '[\'bædli]', 'adv.差的；严重地；恶劣地；极度地', '1. The firm did badly last year. 公司去年生意不好。 2. The child behaved badly at the party. 那孩子在聚会上的表现很差 3. He was wounded badly. 他伤得很厉害。 4. She was injured badly in the accident. 她在这次意外中受到重伤。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('celebrity', '[sə\'lebrəti]', 'n.名人；名誉；社会名流', '1. She became a celebrity overnight. 她一下变成名人了。 2. He was voted the worst dressed celebrity. 大家一致认为他是衣着最差的名人。 3. Celebrity, money and possessions are too often the touchstones for teenagers. 名誉、金钱和财产常常成为青少年们衡量事物的标准。 4. She achieved celebrity status overnight. 她一夜之间成为名流。', '名词: celebrityhood 名词复数: celebrities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('post', '[poʊst]', 'n.职位；邮件；标竿 v.邮递；通知；布置；派遣；急行 adv.快速地', '1. He has no qualifications for the post. 他没有资格担任该职位。 2. Your duties include checking and dispatching the posts. 你的职责是检查和发送邮件。 3. He struggled to run towards the winning post. 他拼命地向获胜标冲去。 4. I would be quite grateful if you would post this letter. 要是你肯寄这封信,我将十分感激。 5. She went post to the bank and cashed the cheque. 她急忙赶到银行,把支票兑换成现金。', '过去式: posted 过去分词: posted 现在分词: posting 第三人称单数: posts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lover', '[\'lʌvər]', 'n.情人；爱好者', '1. His lover is a beautiful girl. 他的情人是一个美丽的女孩。 2. He plucked a rose for his lover. 他为情人摘了一朵玫瑰花。 3. Speaking of his lover, his eyes sparkled. 谈到他的情人时，他的双眼闪烁着光芒。 4. His hapless lover was knocked down by a car. 他那不幸的恋人被汽车撞倒了。', '副词: loverly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('signal', '[\'sɪɡnəl]', 'n.信号；标志 v.(发信号)通知、表示 adj.显著的', '1. A red lamp is often a danger signal. 红灯常常是危险的信号。 2. I corrected my watch by the time signal. 我按报时信号校正我的表。 3. I\'ve called several times, but I keep getting a busy signal. 我打了好几次了,可是一直是忙音。 4. We live too far from the city to get a strong television signal. 我们住的地方离城里太远, 不能收到清晰的电视图像。 5. The police signalled the traffic to move forward slowly. 警察向来往车辆打信号，示意缓慢前行。 6. People speak of Mark Twain as a signal humourous writer. 人们称马克·吐温为杰出的幽默作家。', '名词: signaler 过去式: signaled/signalled 过去分词: signaled/signalled 现在分词: signaling/signalling 第三人称单数: signals/signals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('banana', '[bə\'nænə]', 'n.香蕉', '1. The banana is her favorite fruit. 香蕉是她最喜欢的水果。 2. A banana is mainly pulp, except for its skin. 香蕉除了果皮之外，主要是果肉。 3. I gave Mary an apple in exchange for my favorite banana. 我送给玛丽一个苹果换我最喜欢吃的香蕉。 4. Banana, grape, apple, daisy which of these is the odd one out? 香蕉、葡萄、苹果、雏菊－－这几样东西哪一样与众不同？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('belong', '[bɪ\'lɔːŋ]', 'vi.应归入；属于', '1. The daffodil belongs to the genus Narcissus. 黄水仙是水仙属植物。 2. Those documents belong with the sale report. 那些文件归入销售报告。 3. These boots belong in the closet. 这些靴子应搁在壁橱里。 4. The sentences should belong in a different classification. 这些句子应归入另外一类。', '过去式: belonged 过去分词: belonged 现在分词: belonging 第三人称单数: belongs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('volume', '[\'vɑːljuːm]', 'n.卷；体积；册；音量；容量', '1. This volume contains selections from his early works. 该卷包含了他的早期作品文选。 2. This volume is foxed on the flyleaf. 这卷书的空白页发黄了。 3. A gas has neither definite volume nor definite shape. 气体既无一定体积,又无一定形状。 4. Is that volume still in print? 那册书还能买到吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mortgage', '[\'mɔːrɡɪdʒ]', 'n.按揭；抵押；抵押贷款 vt.抵押', '1. Mortgage Insurance vs Term Life Insurance. 按揭人寿保险。 2. Mortgage is a security interest in real property. 按揭是不动产的一种物权担保。 3. The bank foreclosed a mortgage on the property. 银行取消了抵押人的财产赎回权。 4. We\'re having difficulty keeping up our mortgage payments. 我们难以继续支付分期偿还的抵押贷款。 5. He will have to mortgage his land for a loan. 他不得不将土地抵押来申请贷款。', '过去式: mortgaged 过去分词: mortgaged 现在分词: mortgaging 第三人称单数: mortgages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sympathize', '[\'sɪmpəθaɪz]', 'vi.同情；同感；赞成', '1. We all sympathize with you in your bereavement. 我们对你丧亲之痛表示同情。 2. I sympathize with you; I\'ve had a similar unhappy experience myself. 我很同情你，我自己也有过类似的不幸遭遇。 3. I know you feel angry, and I sympathize. 我知道你感到愤怒，我也有同感。 4. I sympathize with her when she protested. 当她表示抗议时，我与她有同感。', '副词: sympathizingly 名词: sympathizer 过去式: sympathized 过去分词: sympathized 现在分词: sympathizing 第三人称单数: sympathizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refugee', '[ˌrefju\'dʒiː]', 'n.难民', '1. The refugee was condemned to a life of wandering. 这个难民注定要过流浪的生活。 2. The refugee is is lodge in an old army camp. 难民暂时安置在一座旧军营里。 3. The television picture bring home to us all the plight of the refugee. 我们从电视上知道了难民所处的一切困境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stability', '[stə\'bɪləti]', 'n.稳定性；居于修道院', '1. The government has taken a measure to maintain the stability of prices. 政府已经采取了措施以确保物价稳定。 2. The question of stability of an equilibrium is very important. 一个平衡点的稳定性问题是非常重要的。', '名词复数: stabilities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feedback', '[\'fiːdbæk]', 'n.反馈；反馈意见', '1. Did you get any feedback from your clients? 你从顾客那儿得到什么反馈了吗? 2. The writer gets no immediate feedback and simply has to imagine the reader\'s reaction. 作者没有得到及时的反馈,只能猜测读者的反应。 3. Try to give each student some feedback on the task. 针对这项作业,尽量给每位学生提出反馈意见。 4. I\'d appreciate some feedback on my work. 如果有人对我的工作提出意见我将感激不尽。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disrupt', '[dɪs\'rʌpt]', 'vt.干扰；打断；妨碍；使分裂；使破裂', '1. Protesters tried to disrupt the meeting. 抗议者试图扰乱会议。 2. The communication was disrupted by the storm. 暴风雨使交通中断。 3. The bad weather has seriously disrupted supplies of food. 恶劣的天气严重地妨碍了食品的供应。 4. The war seemed likely to disrupt the state. 战争可能使这个国家分裂。', '名词: disrupter 过去式: disrupted 过去分词: disrupted 现在分词: disrupting 第三人称单数: disrupts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('than', '[ðən]', 'conj.比；除…外（用于other等之后）；与其…（用于 rather等之后）；一…就（用于 no sooner等之后） prep.比', '1. She was older than I was. 她年纪比我大。 2. I was inspired to work harder than ever before. 我受激励比以往任何时候都更加努力地工作。 3. This street is four times shorter than that one. 这条街道比那条短四倍。 4. John is more diligent than anyone else in his class. 约翰比班上其他的同学用功。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('language', '[\'læŋɡwɪdʒ]', 'n.语言；语言文字；表达方式', '1. Chinese is my native language. 汉语是我的母语。 2. What languages can you speak? 你会说什么语言？ 3. A dictionary is an invaluable aid in learning a new language. 在学习一种新语言时,辞典是非常有用的工具。 4. She reduced his theories to simple language. 她将他的理论以简单的语言文字表达出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hydrogen', '[\'haɪdrədʒən]', 'n.氢', '1. Hydrogen is highly explosive. 氢极易爆炸。 2. Hydrogen and oxygen are gases. 氢和氧是气体。 3. A molecule of water consists of two atoms of hydrogen and one atom of oxygen. 水分子含有两个氢原子和一个氧原子。', '形容词: hydrogenous 简写符号: H');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('perhaps', '[pər\'hæps]', 'adv.也许；可能', '1. Perhaps this book will prove to be of some use to you in your studies. 也许这本书会对你的研究有用处。 2. As she\'s been ill perhaps she\'ll need some help. 她由于生病可能需要些帮助。 3. Perhaps you left your e-dictionary in the dorm. 可能你将电子词典忘在宿舍里了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('snack', '[snæk]', 'n.小吃；点心 vi.吃点心', '1. We are in a hurry so we have to make doing with a quick snack . 我们时间很紧,只好胡乱吃了顿小吃 2. Usually I only have a snack at lunchtime. 我中午通常只吃点心。 3. Apples are a more nutritional snack than popcorn. 苹果是比爆米花更有营养的零食。 4. If you snack too much, you may get fat. 零食吃的太多,你会长胖的。', '名词: snacker 过去式: snacked 过去分词: snacked 现在分词: snacking 第三人称单数: snacks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('isolate', '[\'aɪsəleɪt]', 'vt.使孤立；隔离 adj.孤立的；单独的', '1. We must isolate the handful of enemies to the maximum. 我们要最大限度地孤立一小撮敌人。 2. We should never isolate ourselves from the masses. 我们永远不能脱离群众。 3. The patient should isolate from his child. 这个病人必须立刻和他的孩子隔离。 4. Scientists have isolated the virus causing the epidemic. 科学家们已分离出引起这种流行病的病毒。 5. It would mean inability to close in and isolate him. 这样，就不能把敌人驱逐到狭小的孤立的阵地上去。', '名词: isolator 过去式: isolated 过去分词: isolated 现在分词: isolating 第三人称单数: isolates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('now', '[naʊ]', 'adv.现在；立刻 conj.既然(与that连用) n.现在；此刻 adj.目前的；现存的 abbr.全国妇女组织(=National Organization of Women)', '1. It is now possible to put a man on the moon. 目前已能将人送到月球上。 2. He is writing a letter now. 他现在正在写信。 3. Now you see I am telling you the truth. 现在你明白我对你讲的是真话了。 4. You can click here to download the file now. 你可以点击这里立刻下载文件。 5. Gas is now widely used for cooking and heating. 现在普遍用煤气烧饭和取暖。 6. Now all are participating in this. 目前的事大家都插手了。', '名词: nowness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evaporate', '[ɪ\'væpəreɪt]', 'v.蒸发；失去水分；消失', '1. If you heat the water,it will evaporate. 你要是把水加热，水会蒸发的。 2. He was afraid his savings would evaporate overnight. 他担心他的储蓄隔夜就蒸发了。 3. Once you have seen fear and depression evaporate in the hot, intense beacon of awareness, you want to repeat the process. 但你发现在热烈的，强度的觉知下，恐惧与压抑消失了，你会想去重复这个过程。 4. Nechyba and Vigdor also show that the peer effects evaporate once they consider the quality of teaching. 内希巴和维格多还表示，一旦他们将教育质量因素纳入考虑范围，同伴效应就消失了。', '形容词: evaporative 副词: evaporatively 名词: evaporation 过去式: evaporated 过去分词: evaporated 现在分词: evaporating 第三人称单数: evaporates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('medical', '[\'medɪkl]', 'adj.医疗的；医学的；医药的；内科的', '1. This is the best medical team in the country. 这是该国最好的医疗队伍。 2. Great advances have been made in medical science. 医疗科学取得巨大的进展。 3. He is engaged in medical research. 他从事于医学的研究。 4. Her medical course was completed ahead of time. 她的医学课程提前完成了。', '副词: medically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mechanic', '[mə\'kænɪk]', 'n.技工；机修工 adj.手工的；（使用）机械的', '1. He worked in a garage as a mechanic. 他在汽车修理厂当技工。 2. The foreman laid out the job for the new mechanic. 领班对新来的技工说明了工作任务。 3. That young man is a motor mechanic. 那个年轻人是一个汽车修理工。 4. The mechanic drained all the oil from the engine. 机械工将发动机中的油全部放走。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adjective', '[\'ædʒɪktɪv]', 'n.形容词 adj.形容词的；不独立的', '1. There are more than 5,000 adjectives in that dictionary. 那本词典中有5000多个形容词。 2. In French the adjective must agree with the noun in number and gender. 法语中形容词必须在数和性上与名词一致。 3. The function of an adjective is to describe or add to the meaning of a noun. 形容词的作用是描述或增加名词的意思。 4. This is an adjective phrase. 这是个形容词短语。', '副词: adjectively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('generalize', '[\'dʒenrəlaɪz]', 'v.概括；归纳；使一般化', '1. It is dangerous to generalize about people. 以偏概全地谈论人是危险的。 2. You cannot generalize about the effects of the drug from one or two cases. 不能根据一两个病例就得出该药是否有效的结论。 3. It is difficult to generalize about job trends in the West. 对西方的就业趋势做一个归纳概括并非易事。 4. Don\'t generalize a conclusion from a few examples. 不要从几个事例中归纳出结论。', '过去式: generalized 过去分词: generalized 现在分词: generalizing 第三人称单数: generalizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('map', '[mæp]', 'n.地图 vt.绘制地图；计划', '1. Paste down the map on the board. 把这张地图用浆糊贴在布告板上。 2. I pricked the map with a pin to show our route. 我用大头针在地图上扎孔标出我们的路线。 3. It is hard to map all the regions of big countries. 为幅员辽阔的国家绘制地图，想把每个地区都详细标注是件困难的事。 4. So for those types of people, the MAP program is very excellent. 因此对于那些类型的人，地图的计划是非常出色的。', '形容词: mappable 名词: mapper 过去式: mapped 过去分词: mapped 现在分词: mapping 第三人称单数: maps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soak', '[soʊk]', 'vt.使浸透；吸入；浸洗；<俚>使喝醉；敲竹杠 vi.浸泡；渗透；渗入；<俚>酗酒 n.浸；湿透；<俚>酒鬼', '1. She soaked the shirt in soapy water. 她把衬衫浸透在肥皂水中。 2. The kind of plant doesn\'t soak the sewage up. 这种植物没有吸入污水。 3. He likes to soak himself in a warm bath. 他喜欢泡洗热水澡。 4. They really soak the tourists in that restaurant. 他们在那家餐厅真的把观光客当成冤大头。 5. Leave the apricots to soak for 20 minutes. 把杏子浸泡20分钟。 6. Give the clothes a long soak before washing. 洗之前先将衣服多泡一些时间。', '名词: soaker 过去式: soaked 过去分词: soaked 现在分词: soaking 第三人称单数: soaks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plate', '[pleɪt]', 'n.碟；金属板；板块；盘 vt.电镀；用金属板固定；为 ... 制印版；给 ... 装钢板', '1. Just a paper? It\'s a small plate of dish. 不就是一篇论文吗,小菜一碟。 2. The doctor inserted a steel plate into his damaged leg. 医生在他受伤的腿中植入了一块钢板。 3. This is apparently related to the tectonic setting of Shandong,namely, the continental margin where the Pacific Plate collided against the Eurasian Plate. 之所以如此,显然与山东所处的大地构造位置,即太平洋板块与欧亚板块相互碰撞的陆缘地带密切相关。 4. He put the apples on a round plate. 他把苹果放在一个圆盘子里。 5. He wanted to plate copper with silver. 他想给铜容器镀银。', '名词: plater 过去式: plated 过去分词: plated 现在分词: plating 第三人称单数: plates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('autonomy', '[ɔː\'tɑːnəmi]', 'n.自治；自治权；自主', '1. The separatist is demanding full autonomy for their state. 分裂主义者在要求他们的州完全自治。 2. They are agitating to assert autonomy. 他们正在鼓吹实行自治。 3. The central government granted autonomy to a national minority. 中央政府对少数民族授予自治权。 4. County boroughs lose their autonomy. 自治郡失去了它们的自治权。', '名词: autonomist 名词复数: autonomies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('leg', '[leɡ]', 'n.腿 vi.用脚走路', '1. The breaking of his right leg made him walk on crutches only. 他右脚的折断使他只有靠拐杖走路。 2. The leg of my tights has torn. 我的裤袜的裤腿破了。 3. The car won\'t start, so we\'ll have to leg it. 汽车发动不起来了,我们只好走着去了。 4. He legged after me. 他在我后面走。', '过去式: legged 过去分词: legged 现在分词: legging 第三人称单数: legs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('typical', '[\'tɪpɪkl]', 'adj.特有的；典型的；有代表性的', '1. Since I\'m here, I\'d like to try a typical dish of this country. 既然来了，我想吃这个国家特有的食物。 2. If they reappear, they manifest themselves in certain typical ways. 一旦它们重复出现就会以特有的方法表现出来。 3. This is a typical bourgeois neighborhood. 这是一个典型的中产阶级地区。 4. They reacted to the appalling weather with typical British stoicism. 他们忍受着恶劣天气的煎熬,表现了英国人典型的坚韧不拔的精神。', '副词: typically 名词: typicalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('desert', '[\'dezərt]', 'n.沙漠；荒地；应得(的惩罚或奖励) v.遗弃；离弃；放弃；擅离职守', '1. Two thirds of the country is dry or desert. 这个国家有三分之二的地方气候干燥,或者是沙漠。 2. Some of them died of thirst in the desert. 他们中有些人在沙漠中渴死了。 3. Water can transform a desert into a garden. 水能把一片不毛之地变成一座花园。 4. The baby\'s mother deserted him soon after giving birth. 那个母亲生下他后不久就把他遗弃了。', '名词: deserter 过去式: deserted 过去分词: deserted 现在分词: deserting 第三人称单数: deserts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('goose', '[ɡuːs]', 'n.鹅；鹅肉；雌鹅；笨蛋；长柄熨斗', '1. The goose hissed at me angrily. 那鹅愤怒地向我发出嘶嘶声。 2. There is some goose left in the bowl. 碗里还剩有点鹅肉。 3. They often have goose at Christmastime. 他们在圣诞节时常常吃鹅肉。 4. This goose is much larger than the duck. 这只母鹅比那只鸭子大多了。', '名词复数: geese 过去式: goosed 过去分词: goosed 现在分词: goosing 第三人称单数: gooses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attend', '[ə\'tend]', 'v.出席；参加；照料；注意；专心于', '1. I shall be attending the meeting. 我会参加会议。 2. During summer vacations some teachers attend seminars at college. 暑假里,一些教师在学院里参加研究班。 3. You\'re going out? But who will attend to the baby? 你要出去?那谁来照料这婴儿。 4. Attend to what your teacher says. 注意听老师的话。', '名词: attender 过去式: attended 过去分词: attended 现在分词: attending 第三人称单数: attends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('group', '[ɡruːp]', 'n.群；组；团体；集团 v.聚合；成群、组；把 ... 聚集；把 ... 分类', '1. She has a very wide group of friends. 她有一大群朋友。 2. A group of boys dashed out of the classroom. 一群男孩子从教室里冲出来。 3. That group harmonizes well. 那一组用和声演唱得很出色。 4. He is a the most brisk young man in this group. 他是这个小组中最活跃的年轻人。 5. They encouraged the workers to group together. 他们鼓励工人们团结起来。', '过去式: grouped 过去分词: grouped 现在分词: grouping 第三人称单数: groups');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('provided', '[prə\'vaɪdɪd]', 'conj.假如；若是 adj.预备好的；提供的 动词provide的过去式和过去分词.', '1. I shall go provided that it doesn\'t rain. 假如不下雨我就去。 2. Provided that you reduce the price, I\'ll take all the goods. 假如你减价,我会买下所有的货物。 3. Provided we have adequate supplies, the enemy can never break in. 若有充足的给养，敌人是打不进来的。 4. I will come provided that I am well enough. 只要我身体好一定来。 5. Please put your litter in the bin provided. 请你把废物扔到预备好的垃圾箱里。 6. The newspaper article provided him with fuel for his speech. 报纸上的这篇文章为他的演讲提供了启发。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('academy', '[ə\'kædəmi]', 'n.学院；学会；专科学校', '1. He is a student in an academy of music. 他是一所音乐学院的学生。 2. He was expelled from the Academy of Sciences. 他被科学院开除了。 3. The Royal Academy is regarded as the sanctuary by artists. 英国皇家艺术学会被艺术家视为圣殿。 4. After graduating from Whittier Academy, my mother went on to Whittier College. 我母亲从惠蒂尔专科学校毕业后，进了惠蒂尔学院。', '名词复数: academies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('minus', '[\'maɪnəs]', 'adj.负的；减的 n.减号；负数；缺点 prep.减去', '1. The temperature is minus twenty degrees. 温度是零下二十度。 2. He seems to have mistaken a plus for a minus. 他似乎把正号误作负号了。 3. A negative value is prefixed by a minus sign. 一个负数将以减号作为前缀。 4. He calculated his gains and losses of money and the result was a minus. 他计算了收益和亏损, 所得结果是个负数。 5. Seven minus three equals four. 七减三等于四。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acclaim', '[ə\'kleɪm]', 'n.喝采；欢呼；赞同 v.欢呼；喝采；称赞', '1. Her performance won her much critical acclaim. 她的表演大获评论界赞颂。 2. He was welcomed with great acclaim. 他受到十分热烈的欢迎。 3. Every four years such acclaim would echo. 这种欢呼，每四年都会来一次。 4. The novel received great acclaim. 这本小说备受赞扬。 5. The whole city turned out to acclaim the winning team. 人们倾城而出为获胜的队欢呼喝彩。', '名词: acclaimer 过去式: acclaimed 过去分词: acclaimed 现在分词: acclaiming 第三人称单数: acclaims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('toast', '[toʊst]', 'n.吐司；烤面包 n.祝酒；祝酒词；被祝酒的人 v.烤；烘 v.(为 ... )祝酒', '1. She put a dab of butter on the toast. 她在吐司上抹了一点黄油。 2. Two toast bread and a cup of coffee. 两个吐司面包，一杯咖啡。 3. We breakfasted on toast and coffee. 我们用的早餐是烤面包片和咖啡。 4. He spread some strawberry jam on his toast. 他把草莓酱涂在烤面包片上。 5. I should like to propose a toast to the bride and bridegroom. 我提议为新娘新郎的幸福乾杯。 6. The burnt toast bread smelled up the whole room. 面包烤焦了，整个房间都充满了焦味。 7. I propose a toast to the health of the guests. 我提议为来宾的健康干一杯。', '过去式: toasted 过去分词: toasted 现在分词: toasting 第三人称单数: toasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disease', '[dɪ\'ziːz]', 'n.疾病 v.使…生病，感染', '1. The disease is still in its primary stage. 这疾病仍然在初发阶段。 2. The entire population was wiped out by the terrible disease. 所有的居民都被可怕的疾病夺去了生命。 3. The rapid spread of the disease is alarming the medical authorities. 这种疾病的迅速蔓延使医疗当局感到忧虑不安。 4. The treatment arrested the growth of the disease. 治疗抑制了病情的发展。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contrive', '[kən\'traɪv]', 'v.图谋；发明；设计；设法做到', '1. The prisoner contrived a way to escape. 囚犯图谋越狱。 2. He contrived to gain their votes. 他施展计谋获得了他们的选票。 3. He contrived a new machine for flying. 他设计了一种新式飞行器。 4. Can you contrive to be at the station by noon? 你能设法在中午前赶到车站吗?', '名词: contriver 过去式: contrived 过去分词: contrived 现在分词: contriving 第三人称单数: contrives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cost', '[kɔːst]', 'n.费用；成本；代价；[律]诉讼费用 v.花费；使付出；使做不愉快的事；估算成本', '1. We calculated the cost of building a new house . 我们计算了造1座新房子的费用。 2. We have to sum up the costs of production. 我们得计算一下生产成本。 3. I\'m determined to attain my purpose at any cost. 我决心不惜任何代价达到目的。 4. He saved his daughter at the cost of his life. 他以牺牲自己的生命挽救了女儿。 5. It will cost 5000 at the lowest computation. 估计最少也值5000英镑。', '形容词: costless 名词: costlessness 过去式: cost 过去分词: cost 现在分词: costing 第三人称单数: costs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bit', '[bɪt]', 'n.少量；小块；片刻；马嚼子；（烟头等的）咬嘴；钻头；钥匙齿；<美口>一角二分半钱；[计]比特 v.给（马等）上嚼口；约束 动词bite的过去式和过去分词', '1. He only put a bit on his plate to make fashion. 他只是拨了一点食物到盘子里做做样子。 2. He assembled the model aircraft bit by bit. 他一块一块地装配飞机模型。 3. Let the broth simmer down a bit more. 让肉汤炖得再久一些吧。 4. The horse was champing the bit . 这匹马格格地咬着马嚼子。', '过去式: bitted 过去分词: bitted 现在分词: bitting 第三人称单数: bits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ask', '[æsk]', 'v.询问；请求；邀请；要求；开价；期待', '1. May I ask a question? 我可以问一个问题吗？ 2. I\'m calling to ask you about the delivery. 我打电话给你,是询问发货的事。 3. He\'ll lend you the money if you ask him. 如果你请求他的话，他就会把钱借给你。 4. It was such a big job that he had to ask for help . 这项工作量太大，他得请求帮助。', '过去式: asked 过去分词: asked 现在分词: asking 第三人称单数: asks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deficiency', '[dɪ\'fɪʃnsi]', 'n.缺乏；不足；缺陷；缺点', '1. I have a slight calcium deficiency. 我有点缺钙。 2. The result in either case is an energy deficiency. 不论哪种情况结果都会导致能量损失。 3. Things will go much better if people of the same trade make up the other\'s deficiency from their own surplus. 同行业之间互通有无，调剂余缺，事情就好办得多了。 4. The deficiency of this plan is very clear and it can\'t possibly succeed. 这项计划的缺陷是很明显的，它不可能成功。', '名词复数: deficiencies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('even', '[\'iːvn]', 'adj.平坦的；平和的；偶数的；相等的 adv.甚至；正当；更；恰好 v.使平坦；相等', '1. A billiard-table must be perfectly even. 台球桌必须十分平. 2. He spoke lightly in even tones. 他以平和的语调温和地讲话。 3. Cars with license plates ending in even numbers must go in this way. 牌照以偶数结尾的汽车必须走这条路。 4. He has an even chance of success. 他成败的机会参半。 5. He didn\'t even have the decency to show me the way. 他甚至连指点我路的礼貌也没有。 6. The path ran steeply up the hill and then evened out. 这条路很陡，到山上就平坦了。', '副词: evenly 名词: evener 过去式: evened 过去分词: evened 现在分词: evening 第三人称单数: evens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kidney', '[\'kɪdni]', 'n.肾；腰子；类型', '1. Each man has a pair of kidneys. 每个人有一对肾脏。 2. Joe has also heard of kidney stones. 乔也听人提到过肾结石。 3. Those two brothers are men of the same kidney. 这两兄弟是同一类型的人。', '名词复数: kidneys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chorus', '[\'kɔːrəs]', 'n.合唱队；歌舞队；齐声说道；副歌部分 vt.合唱', '1. The audience chimed in on the chorus. 听众开始跟合唱队一起唱起来。 2. The chorus is dressed as fairies. 歌舞队的人都装扮成仙子。 3. When I asked questions, they answered up in chorus. 我提问题时,他们迅速齐声回答。 4. The chorus is very catchy to say the least. 副歌部分很容易上口。 5. The papers all chorused the praises of the President. 各报都异口同声地对总统表示赞扬。', '名词复数: choruses 过去式: chorused/chorussed 过去分词: chorused/chorussed 现在分词: chorusing/chorussing 第三人称单数: choruses/chorusses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thing', '[θɪŋ]', 'n.东西；事情 （复）things: 所有物；用具；情况', '1. That was the only thing they could count on. 那是他们唯一依靠的东西。 2. I happened on just the thing I\'d been looking for. 我偶然发现了我一直在寻找的东西。 3. He explained the whole thing from way back. 他把整件事情解释得很透彻。 4. However, teaching is by no means an easy thing. 然而，教书并不是一容易的事情。 5. He put his shaving things into a plastic bag. 他将刮脸用具放入塑料袋内。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hurl', '[hɜːrl]', 'v.用力投掷；愤慨地说出；丢下', '1. The hunter hurled his spear at the tiger. 猎人用力把他的长矛向虎投去。 2. I\'ll hurl him out of the club if he dare tell the secret! 如果他胆敢泄密，我就要把他赶出俱乐部。 3. To hurl abuse is in no way to fight. 谩骂决不是战斗。 4. Businessmen will hurl their money about to get noticed. 商人愿意挥霍钱财来引起注意。', '名词: hurler 过去式: hurled 过去分词: hurled 现在分词: hurling 第三人称单数: hurls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('include', '[ɪn\'kluːd]', 'vt.包括；包含；列入', '1. His writings include poetry and prose. 他的作品包括诗和散文。 2. The graphic arts include calligraphy and lithography. 平面造型艺术包括书法和平版印刷术。 3. Is service included in the bill? 帐单中包含服务费吗？ 4. Please include me in the list. 请把我列入名单中。', '形容词: includable 过去式: included 过去分词: included 现在分词: including 第三人称单数: includes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('racial', '[\'reɪʃl]', 'adj.种族的；人种的', '1. We should not have racial discrimination. 我们不该有种族歧视。 2. This hatred was generated by racial prejudice. 这种仇恨是由种族偏见引起的。 3. Genuine racial equality still seems light-years away. 真正的种族平等似乎仍遥遥无期。 4. A new law has been brought in to discourage racial prejudice. 一项反对种族歧视的新法律已被提出。', '副词: racially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oppose', '[ə\'poʊz]', 'v.反对；对抗；使对立', '1. It was courageous of him to oppose his chief. 他敢反对他的上司，真是勇敢。 2. The rabbles met on the square to oppose their new mayor. 平民们在广场上集会反对他们的新市长。 3. They opposed the government\'s new policies. 他们反对政府的新政策。 4. We\'re firmly opposed to the practice of powerpolitics between nations. 我们强烈反对在国与国之间实行强权政治。', '名词: opposer 过去式: opposed 过去分词: opposed 现在分词: opposing 第三人称单数: opposes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contrary', '[\'kɑːntreri]', 'adj.相反的；截然不同的；执拗的 n.反面；相反', '1. Hot and cold are contrary terms. 热与冷是相反的词语。 2. My sister\'s taste in dresses is contrary to my own. 在服装方面，我妹妹的爱好和我完全不同。 3. Mrs. Smith is too contrary to make friends easily. 史密斯太太过于固执而不易交朋友。 4. Cruelty is the contrary of kindness. 残忍是仁慈的反面。', '副词: contrarily 名词: contrariness 名词复数: contraries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('judge', '[dʒʌdʒ]', 'n.法官；裁判 v.断定；判断；审判', '1. He is an impartial judge. 他是一位公正的法官。 2. At the end of the trial, the judge summed up. 审讯结束后,法官作了总结。 3. The judges\' decision is final. 裁判的决定为最终决定。 4. I judge him to be about 40. 我断定他有40来岁。', '过去式: judged 过去分词: judged 现在分词: judging 第三人称单数: judges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trap', '[træp]', 'n.圈套；陷阱；困境；双轮轻便马车；U（或S）型管道；防臭瓣 v.设圈套；陷入（困境）', '1. The police set a trap to catch the thief. 警察设下了捉拿窃贼的圈套。 2. The only thing the wolf could do was climbing up to the ground from the trap. 那只狼惟一能做的就是从陷阱里爬到地面上来。 3. To break out of the poverty trap they need help from the government. 为了摆脱贫困的处境，他们需要政府的帮助。 4. She didn\'t say anything about a trap. 她根本没提马车的事。 5. By clever questioning they trapped him into making a confession. 他们用巧妙的提问诱使他招认了。', '过去式: trapped 过去分词: trapped 现在分词: trapping 第三人称单数: traps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refrain', '[rɪ\'freɪn]', 'v.抑制；避免；克制 n.副歌；叠句；重复', '1. Sunlight can refrain the growth of melatonin in the body. 阳光能抑制身体中褪黑激素的生长。 2. I carefully refrained from looking at him. 我留意着避免朝他看。 3. I wish he would refrain from scattering his ash all over the carpet. 我希望他不要将烟灰往地毯上乱弹。 4. You must refrain from smoking in this area. 在这个区域，你必须克制自己不抽烟。 5. Will you all join in singing the refrain, please? 请大家一道来唱副歌好吗?', '名词: refrainer 过去式: refrained 过去分词: refrained 现在分词: refraining 第三人称单数: refrains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accommodation', '[əˌkɑːmə\'deɪʃn]', 'n.膳宿；和解；住处；适应', '1. There travelling students found accommodation at moderate terms. 旅游的学生们感到那儿的膳宿费是公道的。 2. If labour and management don\'t reach an accommodation there will be a strike. 如果劳资双方达不成妥协，就会发生罢工。 3. We can provide accommodation for six people at a push. 如情况需要，我们可以安排六个人的住处。 4. Hotel accommodation was scarce during the Olympic Games. 奥运会期间，旅馆房间很难找。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('marriage', '[\'mærɪdʒ]', 'n.结婚；婚姻；紧密结合', '1. The news of their marriage knocked me for a loop. 他们结婚的消息使我大吃一惊。 2. It was a pleasant surprise to learn of her marriage. 得知她结婚是件令人惊喜的事。 3. Marriage is an institution in most societies. 婚姻是大多数社会早已确立的制度。 4. Marriage is for life. 婚姻是终身大事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mingle', '[\'mɪŋɡl]', 'vt.使混合；使结合 vi.交往；联合；混在一起', '1. You can not mingle oil and water . 你不能把油和水混合在一起。 2. She accepted the money with mingled feelings. 她悲喜交集地收下了这笔钱。 3. The two rivers mingle their waters here. 这两条河在这里汇合起来了。 4. He is too shy to mingle with others. 他由于太内向而怯于与他人交往。', '名词: mingler 过去式: mingled 过去分词: mingled 现在分词: mingling 第三人称单数: mingles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lord', '[lɔːrd]', 'n.君王；勋爵；统治者；[大写]上帝；主 v.使…成君主；支配；作威作福', '1. I was full of curiosity to meet Lord Marchmain. 我心里充满了要见马奇梅因勋爵的好奇心。 2. The Lord bless thee and keep thee. 主祝福你，照顾你。 3. She refused to be lorded over. 她拒绝从命。 4. He likes to lord it over the junior staff. 他喜欢对下级职员逞威风。', '过去式: lorded 过去分词: lorded 现在分词: lording 第三人称单数: lords');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surname', '[\'sɜːrneɪm]', 'n.姓；绰号 vt.冠姓；以别名称呼', '1. What is your surname? 你的姓是什么？ 2. Jones is a common surname. 琼斯是个很普通的姓。 3. On marriage most women still take their husband\'s surname. 一旦结婚,大部分妇女会用丈夫的姓。 4. It\'s not a good habit to surname for others. 给别人起绰号可不好。 5. It\'s not a good habit to surname for others. 给别人起绰号可不好。', '过去式: surnamed 过去分词: surnamed 现在分词: surnaming 第三人称单数: surnames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heart', '[hɑːrt]', 'n.心；内心；中心；要点；红桃 v.将…记在心里，铭记；鼓励', '1. My heart was thumping with excitement. 我激动得心怦怦跳。 2. Mr Jones has a long history of heart trouble. 琼斯先生有长期的心脏病史。 3. He has a kind heart. 他心地善良。 4. Let\'s get to the heart of the matter. 让我们谈谈这件事的核心部分。', '过去式: hearted 过去分词: hearted 现在分词: hearting 第三人称单数: hearts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loop', '[luːp]', 'n.环；圈；回路；环形线路 vt.以圈结；以环连结；使 ... 成环（圈） vi.形成环；环形运动', '1. This control may be closed loop or open loop. 控制可以是闭环的也可以是开环的。 2. Her wavy hair fell in loose wisps and loops upon her shoulders. 她那一头波浪般的长发一簇簇一圈圈地散垂在肩上。 3. He looped a scarf around his neck. 他把围巾在脖子上围成一圈。 4. I have to loop the wooden pegs around the garden. 我不得不用木桩来环住园地。', '过去式: looped 过去分词: looped 现在分词: looping 第三人称单数: loops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('solidarity', '[ˌsɑːlɪ\'dærəti]', 'n.团结', '1. Their sense of solidarity is very low. 他们的团结观念非常薄弱。 2. The strike fostered a sense of solidarity among the workers. 罢工促进了工人之间的团结。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dust', '[dʌst]', 'n.灰尘；尘土；粉尘 vt.去掉 ... 的灰尘；撒粉末于 vi.除尘', '1. The mirror is covered with a film of dust. 镜子蒙上了一层灰尘。 2. A thick layer of dust lay on the furniture. 家具上覆盖着一层厚厚的灰尘。 3. The truck left clouds of dust in its wake. 车后扬起了一阵尘土。 4. She knocks the dust out of her coat. 她打掉外套上的尘土。 5. I used a piece of rag to dust the wooden furniture. 我用一块抹布擦拭木制家具上的灰尘。 6. It\'s dusty so we have to dust every day. 灰尘多,所以我们必须每天掸灰除尘。', '过去式: dusted 过去分词: dusted 现在分词: dusting 第三人称单数: dusts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flexible', '[\'fleksəbl]', 'adj.柔韧的；灵活的；易弯曲的；可变通的', '1. This tube is flexible but tough. 这管子柔软但很坚固。 2. We need a foreign policy that is more flexible. 我们需要一个更为灵活的外交政策。 3. People use Java because it is flexible and runs on multiple platforms. 人们使用Java是因为它的灵活性及在多种平台上可以运行。 4. Leather and rubber are flexible, glass and iron are not. 皮革和橡胶都是易弯曲的，玻璃和铁则不然。', '副词: flexibly 名词: flexibility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('progress', '[\'prɑːɡres]', 'n.进步；发展；前进 v.进步；发展；缓速前进；促进', '1. The student is showing rapid progress in his studies. 这个学生学习上进步很快。 2. Physics has made enormous progress in this century. 本世纪物理学的发展突飞猛进。 3. They made slow progress towards the mountaintop. 他们向山顶缓慢地前进。 4. He continues to progress in his studies. 他的学业继续取得进步。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('handsome', '[\'hænsəm]', 'adj.可观的；英俊的；慷慨大方的；灵巧的', '1. The waitress received a handsome tip. 女侍者收到了数量可观的小费。 2. The deal netted him a handsome profit. 这笔交易让他捞到了可观的利润。 3. He is a reporter on the news,and draws a handsome screw. 他是新闻记者，领取可观的薪水。 4. Her bridegroom is a handsome young man. 她的新郎是一个英俊的年轻人。', '副词: handsomely 比较级: handsomer 最高级: handsomest 名词: handsomeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suitable', '[\'suːtəbl]', 'adj.适宜的；合适的', '1. These films are suitable for adults only. 这些电影只适宜成人观看。 2. All the students are assigned to suitable jobs. 所有的学生都分到了合适的工作。 3. The director is looking for a suitable locale for his new film. 导演在为新片物色合适的拍摄场地。', '副词: suitably 名词: suitability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('item', '[\'aɪtəm]', 'n.项目；条款；一件商品（或物品）；一则或一条新闻 adv.也', '1. Let us go on to the next item on the agenda. 让我们继续讨论议程上的下一个项目。 2. The item of the contract still stands now. 该项合同条款现在依然有效。 3. Gone forever are the days when this item sold well. 这一品种畅销的日子一去不复返了。 4. Are there any interesting news items in the paper this morning? 今天早晨报上有什么有趣的新闻吗？ 5. The truck you also see is a signature item. 你可以看到的这种卡车也是一种标志。', '过去式: itemed 过去分词: itemed 现在分词: iteming 第三人称单数: items');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('away', '[ə\'weɪ]', 'adv.离开；远离；在远处；一直；朝另一个方向；消失 adj.不在的；遥远的；[棒]出局的；客场的', '1. He lives 3 miles away from here. 他住在距离这里三英里的地方。 2. I hope to get away early in the morning. 我希望一早就动身离开。 3. He lives in retirement, away from everyone. 他远离大家隐居着。 4. I tried to keep the child away from the pool. 我设法使孩子远离水池。 5. The neighbors are away. 邻居不在家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fell', '[fel]', 'vt.砍伐；击倒 n.丘原；沼泽地 adj.凶残的；毁灭性的 动词fall的过去式.', '1. The lumberman will fell these great trees. 这位伐木工将砍伐掉这些大树。 2. He felled his enemy with a single blow. 他一拳将他的敌人打倒了。 3. This is the famous Lakeland Fells. 这就是著名的莱克兰荒野。 4. The wind and rain beat down on me, and I fell down several times, but finally I arrived at a long, low house, standing rather isolated in the middle of the moor. 风裹着雨打在我的身上，我跌倒了好几次，但终于还是走到了一幢孤零零立在沼泽地中间的长长的矮房子前。 5. He was struck by a fell blow to the head. 他的头部受到了重击。 6. The girl lost her balance and fell off the balance beam. 小女孩失去了平衡，从平衡木上摔了下来。', '形容词: fellable 名词: fellness 过去式: felled 过去分词: felled 现在分词: felling 第三人称单数: fells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('into', '[\'ɪntə]', 'prep.到 ... 里；进入；朝；除；<口>对...有兴趣', '1. An idea popped into his mind like a flash. 他头脑里突然闪过一个念头。 2. Nothing will induce me to jump into the icy water. 我怎么也不会想跳进这冰冷的水里。 3. The thief broke into the house during the night. 小偷在夜间破门进入住宅。 4. Driving into the sun, we had to shade our eyes. 车朝着有太阳的方向开,我们只好遮挡着眼睛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hen', '[hen]', 'n.母鸡；雌禽', '1. The hen sits for most of the day. 这只母鸡整天大部分时间都在抱窝。 2. The hen laid a large brown egg. 这只母鸡下了一个大红皮蛋。 3. The hen tucked her head under her wing. 那母鸡把头缩在翅膀下。 4. The hen clucked when calling her chickens. 母鸡唤小鸡时，发出咯咯的叫声。', '形容词: hennish 副词: hennishly 名词: hennishness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('terror', '[\'terər]', 'n.恐怖；惊骇；<口>令人惧怕或讨厌的人或事物', '1. Her face worked as she stared at him in terror. 她惊恐地注视着他，脸也吓得抽动起来。 2. She let out a scream of terror. 她发出恐怖的叫喊。 3. His terror is so great that he can do nothing. 他惊骇万分以致什么事都不能做。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('south', '[saʊθ]', 'n.南；南方 adj.南方的 adv.在南方；向南方；自南方', '1. He suggested that we should make for the south. 他建议我们往南走。 2. They lived in a room facing the south. 他们住在一间面南的房间里。 3. A humid wind blew from the south. 湿润的风从南方吹来。 4. He is used to the soft climate of the south. 他习惯于南方温暖的气候。 5. Large numbers of birds migrate south every winter. 每年冬季大量的鸟类迁徙南方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tune', '[tuːn]', 'n.曲调；调子；和谐；协调；数量 vt.为 ... 调音；调整 vi.调音；调整频率', '1. He played a tune on the violin. 他用小提琴演奏了一首曲子。 2. She was humming a tune to herself. 她自个儿哼著小调。 3. The violin is not quite in tune with the piano. 这小提琴跟钢琴的调子不太和谐。 4. His ideas are in tune with the times. 他的思想适合时代的潮流。 5. The orchestra tuned their instruments. 乐队在给乐器调音。 6. Please tune up your instruments before class. 请在上课前调好乐器的音调。', '过去式: tuned 过去分词: tuned 现在分词: tuning 第三人称单数: tunes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interact', '[ˌɪntər\'ækt]', 'vi.相互作用；相互联系；相互影响；互动', '1. These factors interact intimately and cannot be separated. 这些因素相互之间紧密联系，不能分开。 2. Mother and baby interact in a very complex way. 母亲与婴儿以非常复杂的方式相互影响。 3. Economists also study how people interact with one another. 经济学家也研究人们之间的相互影响。 4. Teachers should interact with students more frequently in the class. 老师应该在课堂上与学生有更多的互动。', '过去式: interacted 过去分词: interacted 现在分词: interacting 第三人称单数: interacts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interesting', '[\'ɪntrəstɪŋ]', 'adj.有趣的；引人入胜的', '1. This book is interesting. 这本书很有趣。 2. There is an interesting program on television tonight. 今天晚上有一个有趣的电视节目。 3. She is an interesting person but her husband is a real nothing. 她是个很有趣的人，但是她的先生却一无是处。 4. Your interesting report raises several important queries. 你的精彩报告引出了几个重要问题。', '副词: interestingly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('restore', '[rɪ\'stɔːr]', 'vt.恢复；归还；复原', '1. The military government promised to restore democracy within one year. 军人政府答应在一年内重新建立民主体制。 2. Drastic measures will have to be taken to restore order. 为恢复秩序必须采取严厉措施。 3. The police must try to restore order. 警方必须努力恢复治安。 4. The new manager\'s job is to restore the company to profitability. 新经理的工作是让这家公司能恢复盈利状况。', '名词: restorer 过去式: restored 过去分词: restored 现在分词: restoring 第三人称单数: restores');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('positive', '[\'pɑːzətɪv]', 'adj.积极的；肯定的；明确的；正面的；正数的；阳性的 n.正面；正数；正片；[语]原级', '1. He has a positive attitude towards life. 他对生活持有积极的态度。 2. We regret out inability to let you know anything positive concerning the above firm. 很抱歉，我方无法让您了解上述公司任何肯定的资料。 3. We still don\'t have a positive answer as to how he died. 他究竟是如何死的，我们还未得出明确的答案。 4. These developments will have a positive effect on the stability of our financial market. 这些发展对稳定我们的金融市场会产生正面的作用。 5. The relationship with this supplier is positive. 我与供应商的关系是正面的。', '副词: positively 名词: positiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sand', '[sænd]', 'n.沙；沙子；沙滩；黄灰色 vt.撒沙；打磨；以沙掩盖', '1. Dry sand absorbs water. 干沙吸收水份。 2. Ouch! The sand is so hot! I can burn my feet. 哎哟！沙子这么烫！会烫伤脚的。 3. A grain of sand made my right eye tear. 一粒沙子弄得我右眼淌泪。 4. The children on the sand were shouting with excitement. 沙滩上的孩子们兴奋得大喊大叫。 5. The roads were sanded after the snowstorm. 道路在暴风雪之后铺上了沙子。', '过去式: sanded 过去分词: sanded 现在分词: sanding 第三人称单数: sands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tradition', '[trə\'dɪʃn]', 'n.传统；惯例', '1. We shall carry forward the revolutionary tradition. 我们应该发扬革命传统。 2. In many countries young people still keep up the tradition that women will get married in a long white dress. 许多国家里，年轻人仍保持着妇女结婚时穿白色长礼服的传统。 3. They still follow the tradition of their fathers. 他们仍然继承著他们祖先的传统。 4. The older generation are respectful of tradition. 年老的一辈尊重传统。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pastime', '[\'pæstaɪm]', 'n.消遣；娱乐', '1. His favorite pastime is tinkering with old radios. 他最喜欢的消遣就是整修老旧的收音机。 2. Dancing is mary\'s favourite pastime. 跳舞是玛丽最喜欢的一种娱乐方式。 3. In fact, it\'s something of a national pastime. 事实上，在某种意义上它是全国人民的娱乐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reproduce', '[ˌriːprə\'duːs]', 'v.再生；复制；生殖', '1. Lobsters can reproduce a lost limb. 龙虾能使失去的肢体重新再生出来。 2. Some animals can reproduce lost parts of their bodies. 有些动物能再生身体上失去的部分。 3. This copier can reproduce colour photographs. 这台复印机可复制彩色照片。 4. We shall reproduce this handbook in full. 我们将把这本手册完整地复制一份。', '形容词: reproducible 名词: reproducer 过去式: reproduced 过去分词: reproduced 现在分词: reproducing 第三人称单数: reproduces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recall', '[rɪ\'kɔːl]', 'n.回忆；取消；召回 vt.召回；恢复；回想起；唤起；与 ... 相似', '1. Do you have any recall of that meeting? 你还记得那次会见吗? 2. The new law is now established beyond recall. 新法律现已制定，不得撤销。 3. The experiment sample the raw test of novel Hero Borns to test for times , and it acquires an accuracy of 86.93% , while an recall rate of 91.83%. 实验对小说《英雄出世》的生文本进行了多次抽样测试 4. With the impulse of \"mercantile system\", the Occident adjust their policy one after the other, recall Jew in succession. 在“重商主义”政策的积极推动下,西欧各国相继调整对犹政策,纷纷召回犹太人。', '形容词: recallable 过去式: recalled 过去分词: recalled 现在分词: recalling 第三人称单数: recalls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reputation', '[ˌrepju\'teɪʃn]', 'n.好名声；声誉，名声，名气', '1. This store has an excellent reputation for fair dealing. 这家商店因公平交易而获好名声。 2. He has not too good a reputation in the matter of honesty. 就诚实而言, 他的名声不太好。 3. He trades on his father\'s reputation. 他用他父亲的名誉牟利。 4. He spotted his reputation by lying repeatedly. 他因反复说谎而败坏了自己的名声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wooden', '[\'wʊdn]', 'adj.木制的；生硬笨拙的', '1. There is a wooden porch over the sidewalk. 人行道上有一个木制的门廊。 2. He has two big round new Chinese wooden tables. 他有两张新的中国式的木制的大圆桌。', '副词: woodenly 名词: woodenness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abide', '[ə\'baɪd]', 'v.遵守；忍受；坚持', '1. Everyone must abide by the law. 所有的人都应遵守法律。 2. Once you make a promise, you must abide by it. 一旦你许诺,你必须遵守你的诺言。 3. She can\'t abide that man. 她不能忍受那个人。 4. I cannot abide the loud noise anymore. 我再也无法忍受这么大的噪音。', '名词: abider 过去式: abode/abided 过去分词: abode/abided 现在分词: abiding 第三人称单数: abides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cucumber', '[\'kjuːkʌmbər]', 'n.黄瓜', '1. Have some cucumber. 吃点黄瓜吧。 2. I like to eat cucumber sandwiches. 我喜欢吃有黄瓜的三明治。 3. In our garden we have egg-plants, cucumber and potato. 在我们的菜园里，我们种了茄子，黄瓜和土豆。 4. I would like a cucumber salad for an appetizer. 我要一份黄瓜沙拉作为开胃菜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('warfare', '[\'wɔːrfer]', 'n.战争；冲突', '1. This is as true of warfare as it is of diplomacy. 这是真正的战争，就像刚才提到的外交。 2. Warfare has always expedited military technology. 战争总是在促进军事科技的进步。 3. In countries like Nigeria they precipitate coups or tribal warfare. 而在尼日利亚这样的国家，则敏感到会导致政变和部族冲突。 4. That intensified the conflict, as the Tatars were now unrestrained in their warfare against Khmelnytsky. 这让冲突更为激烈，鞑靼人在与赫梅利尼茨基交战时更加不受限制。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chimney', '[\'tʃɪmni]', 'n.烟囱', '1. The explosion toppled the old chimney. 这次爆炸把那个旧烟囱给炸倒了。 2. The chimney is almost choked up with soot. 烟囱几乎被烟垢堵住了。 3. The smoke from chimney is spreading out in the sky. 烟囱冒出的烟正在空中散开。 4. I can hear a bird fluttering in the chimney. 我听见一只鸟在烟囱里扑扑地拍翅。', '名词复数: chimneys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('continuous', '[kən\'tɪnjuəs]', 'adj.连续的；继续的；连绵不断的', '1. The atmosphere is a continuous layer of gases. 大气圈是连续的气体层。 2. We\'ve had three weeks of continuous rain. 我们这里连续三周下雨不停。 3. I look forward to your continuous support. 我期望各位继续的支持。 4. War had been literally continuous. 战争几乎连绵不断。', '副词: continuously 名词: continuousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('storage', '[\'stɔːrɪdʒ]', 'n.保管；贮藏；仓库；保管费；[计]存储器', '1. The best place for storage of money is a bank. 银行是存钱最好的地方。 2. The cave can be used for storage. 洞穴可以用来贮藏东西。 3. You should place the goods in storage. 你应该把货物贮藏起来 4. His furniture is in storage while he finds a new house. 他在找新房子时把家具存放在仓库里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quite', '[kwaɪt]', 'adv.相当；完全；十分；很', '1. He was quite young. 他相当年轻。 2. The boy has quite recovered. 这男孩已彻底恢复健康。 3. I don\'t quite follow you, sir. 先生, 对您的意思我没有完全领会。 4. This is a good system but quite expensive. 这种装置很好,但十分昂贵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preceding', '[priː\'siːdɪŋ]', 'adj.在前的；在先的', '1. This point has been dealt with in the preceding paragraph. 这一点在前面一段里已经交代过了。 2. In the years immediately preceding the outbreak of war in1939, Hitler succeeded in annexing various parts of Europe to Germany without firing a shot. 在1939年大战爆发的前几年，希特勒没开一抢而成功地把欧洲许多地区并吞为德国领土。 3. He had been in Cuba the preceding summer. 去年夏天他曾在古巴。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grief', '[ɡriːf]', 'n.悲痛；忧伤', '1. She uttered a wail of grief. 她悲痛地大声尖叫。 2. She was prostrate with grief. 她因悲痛而一蹶不振。 3. The poor woman was buried in grief after her son died. 这个可怜的妇人在儿子死后一直沉浸在悲痛之中。 4. No words can express my grief. 我的忧伤无法用语言表达。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stare', '[ster]', 'v.盯着看；凝视 n.凝视', '1. She stared him into silence. 她把他盯得不吭声了。 2. They all stared with astonishment. 他们全都惊讶地瞪着眼。 3. It\'s impolite to stare at people. 盯着看人是不礼貌的。 4. You can enjoy its beauty each time you stare at its wonderment. 每当你凝视它，你都能重温旧梦。 5. Peter looked at them with glazy stare. 彼得用呆滞的目光凝视他们。', '名词: starer 过去式: stared 过去分词: stared 现在分词: staring 第三人称单数: stares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('word', '[wɜːrd]', 'n.单词；消息；话语；诺言 v.用词语表达', '1. Could we have a word before you go to the meeting? 你去开会之前，咱们能私下说句话吗？ 2. Tell me what happened in your own words. 用你自己的话把发生的事情告诉我。 3. My friend sent word that he was well. 我朋友捎来口信说他很好。', '过去式: worded 过去分词: worded 现在分词: wording 第三人称单数: words');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('emperor', '[\'empərər]', 'n.皇帝', '1. The emperor was actually a political eunuch. 那个皇帝实际上没有政治实权。 2. The emperor conferred a title on the brave soldier. 皇上授予这勇敢的士兵一头衔。 3. He knelt in front of the emperor with a look of entreaty. 他面带恳求的神态跪在皇帝面前。 4. The general overthrew the last emperor of that country and established a public. 将军推翻了那个国家的最后一个皇帝，建立了共和国。', '名词: emperorship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spouse', '[spaʊs]', 'n.配偶', '1. He never mentioned his spouse. 他从来不提自己的妻子。 2. They get free ticket for their spouse. 他们为家属领到了免费的票。 3. What is your spouse immigration status? 你配偶的移民身份是什么? 4. Your spouse\'s family are your -in-laws. 你配偶的家人是你的姻亲。', '过去式: spoused 过去分词: spoused 现在分词: spousing 第三人称单数: spouses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assassinate', '[ə\'sæsəneɪt]', 'v.暗杀，行刺', '1. A plot to assassinate the President was uncovered. 暗杀总统的阴谋被发觉。', '形容词: assassinative 名词: assassination 过去式: assassinated 过去分词: assassinated 现在分词: assassinating 第三人称单数: assassinates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('destruction', '[dɪ\'strʌkʃn]', 'n.破坏；毁灭', '1. It will cause pollution and the destruction of our seas and oceans. 这会引起污染，破坏我们的海洋和江河。 2. Scientific knowledge was perverted to help cause destruction and war. 科学知识被滥用于破坏和战争。 3. Gambling was his destruction. 赌博把他毁了。 4. We must not bring mass destruction on ourselves by waging an atomic world war. 我们千万不要发动世界核子战争而自招集体毁灭。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blossom', '[\'blɑːsəm]', 'n.花；开花；全盛期 vi.开花；成长', '1. The sunshine will bring out the blossom. 阳光将使花朵开放。 2. The tree was covered with beautiful pink blossom. 这树开满了美丽的粉红色的花。 3. The apple trees are in blossom. 苹果树正在开花。 4. There are many pear trees covered in blossom. 那里有许多开满花的梨树。 5. The apple trees are blossoming. 苹果树正在开花。', '形容词: blossomy 过去式: blossomed 过去分词: blossomed 现在分词: blossoming 第三人称单数: blossoms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('permit', '[pər\'mɪt]', 'n.许可证；执照 v.允许；许可', '1. You can\'t work here without a work permit. 你没有许可证就不能在这里工作。 2. He said that if he had a permit he could get a job. 他说如果他有执照就能找到工作。 3. I\'ll come after the meeting if time permits. 如果时间许可的话，我开完会就来。 4. You are not permitted to smoke here. 此处不许吸烟。', '名词: permittee 过去式: permitted 过去分词: permitted 现在分词: permitting 第三人称单数: permits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('career', '[kə\'rɪr]', 'n.生涯；职业；事业 vi.猛冲；飞跑', '1. His early career was not a great success. 他早期的生涯并不很成功。 2. She is a career woman rather than a housewife. 她是职业妇女而不是家庭主妇。 3. Young as I am,I already know what career I want to follow. 我虽然还小,可是对要从事的职业已胸有成竹了。 4. His career took off in 1997. 1997年他的事业开始有了起色。 5. He careered down the road on a bicycle. 他骑着自行车沿路飞奔而去。', '过去式: careered 过去分词: careered 现在分词: careering 第三人称单数: careers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conclude', '[kən\'kluːd]', 'vt.推断出；缔结；使结束 vi.结束；总结；作决定；作协议', '1. From his appearance we may safely conclude that he is a chain smoker. 从他的外表，我们可以有把握地断定他烟抽得很凶。 2. The two countries are reported to have concluded a military convention. 据报导,这两个国家已缔结军事协定。 3. He conclude the negotiation with dispatch. 他迅速结束谈判。 4. The concert concluded with the National Anthem. 音乐会最后以演奏国歌结束。', '名词: concluder 过去式: concluded 过去分词: concluded 现在分词: concluding 第三人称单数: concludes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('few', '[fjuː]', 'adj.很少的；少数的；几个 pron.少数 n.少量', '1. We saw few students there. 我们在那儿几乎没看见学生。 2. The sunny intervals we were promised have been few and far between. 我们原可望能有几阵晴天，结果却很稀少。 3. Very few girls went to school then. 那时几乎没有女孩子去上学。 4. Only a few of my friends were informed about it. 这件事只有我的几个朋友知道 5. Few of us have his address. 我们中几乎没有人知道他的地址。', '比较级: fewer 最高级: fewest 名词: fewness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('approximate', '[ə\'prɑːksɪmət]', 'adj.近似的；大约的 v.接近；约等于', '1. This is just an approximate figure. 这仅仅是个近似值。 2. We are entirely justified in using the approximate theory. 我们用近似理论完全正当。 3. He spent approximate two hours searching the photo. 他用了大约两小时来寻找这张照片. 4. The approximate number of students in the school is 300. 这所学校的学生数大约为300人。 5. Production costs approximate to $100,000 . 生产成本接近十万美元。', '副词: approximately 过去式: approximated 过去分词: approximated 现在分词: approximating 第三人称单数: approximates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trademark', '[\'treɪdmɑːrk]', 'n.商标；特点', '1. Nobody has a trademark on it so the name is open. 尚无人用此商标，所以这个名字可以使用。 2. Have you noticed the trademark on the bottle? 你注意到瓶子上的商标了吗？', '过去式: trademarked 过去分词: trademarked 现在分词: trademarking 第三人称单数: trademarks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sphere', '[sfɪr]', 'n.范围；领域；球；球体；天体 vt.形成球体；包围；围绕', '1. It belongs to the ideological sphere. 这属于意识形态范围。 2. The scientist is distinguished in many spheres of knowledge. 这位科学家在许多知识领域中都是杰出的。 3. Suddenly, out in the night sky, a bright sphere flashed into view. 突然，外面的夜空上有一个闪光的球映入眼帘。 4. The earth is an oblate sphere. 地球是一扁圆球体。', '名词: sphericity 过去式: sphered 过去分词: sphered 现在分词: sphering 第三人称单数: spheres');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('steward', '[\'stuːərd]', 'n.乘务员；管家；干事；管理员 v.做乘务员；管理', '1. His neighbor is a chief steward. 他的邻居是一个乘务员领班。 2. We thanked the steward for his good service. 我们感谢了乘务员所提供的优质服务。 3. Sometimes he sent his house steward in his place. 有时他派管家替他去。 4. The stewards will inspect the course to see if racing is possible. 那些干事将检视赛马场看是否适宜比赛。 5. He was selected to steward a team. 他被指派经管球队。', '名词: stewardship 过去式: stewarded 过去分词: stewarded 现在分词: stewarding 第三人称单数: stewards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rumor', '[\'ruːmə]', 'n.谣言；传闻 vt.谣传 =<英>rumour', '1. I\'m rather bored by the rumor. 这谣传我真听厌烦了。 2. Despite persistent denials, the rumor continued to spread. 尽管一再否认，谣言还是不胫而走。 3. A rumor went forth that the price of eggs would be raised soon. 谣传近期鸡蛋要涨价。 4. The rumor was without foundation. 那条谣言毫无根据。 5. He is rumored to have escaped to Dublin. 据说他已逃往都柏林。', '过去式: rumored 过去分词: rumored 现在分词: rumoring 第三人称单数: rumors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aluminum', '[ə\'luːmɪnəm]', 'n.铝 =aluminium（英）.', '1. A metallurgical coating process in which iron or steel is immersed in a powder of another metal, such as zinc, chromium, or aluminum, and heated to a temperature below the melting point of either. 渗碳处理一种冶金镀膜工序，在此工序中把钢或铁浸入另一种金属如锌、铬或铝的粉剂里，并加热至这一金属的熔点温度以下 2. She put some noodles in the aluminum saucepan. 她在铝锅里下了些面条。 3. Aluminum is a kind of light silvery metal. 铝是一种轻薄并呈银色的金属。 4. Aluminum foil can be used for wrapping food. 铝箔用于包装食物。', '简写符号: Al');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('benefit', '[\'benɪfɪt]', 'n.利益；津贴；义演；保险金；借助 vt.有益于；得益', '1. It was for the benefit of your company that we did that. 我们这样做都是为了你们公司的利益。 2. Applications for unemployment benefits dropped last month. 上个月申请失业津贴的人数下降了。 3. A benefit performance will be held tonight. 今晚有义演。 4. The unemployed are entitled to receive other unemployment insurance benefits during the period of receiving unemployment insurance compensation. 失业人员在领取失业保险金期间,按照规定同时享受其他失业保险待遇。 5. The new hospital will benefit the entire community. 新医院将有益于整个社区。', '过去式: benefited/benefitted 过去分词: benefited/benefitted 现在分词: benefiting/benefitting 第三人称单数: benefits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('youth', '[juːθ]', 'n.青年时期；青春；青年', '1. In his youth, he had shown great promise. 他在青少年时代就显得很有出息。 2. He mused over memories of his youth. 他重温青年时期的往事。 3. Youth glided past without our awareness. 青春在我们不知不觉中逝去。 4. I can\'t bear young people casting away their youth. 我无法忍受年轻人虚掷青春。', '名词复数: youths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deal', '[diːl]', 'n.协定；交易；大量 v.应付；分配；处理；交易；经营', '1. We did a deal with the management on overtime. 在加班问题上我们与管理部门达成一项协议。 2. After weeks of negotiating, they\'re finalizing the deal today. 经过几周协商,他们今天会搞定交易。 3. In addition to leaves, these animals eat a great deal of fruit. 除了树叶之外,这些动物还吃大量的水果。 4. If the worst comes to the worst, we can always deal with it. 事情再糟,我们总可以应付。', '过去式: dealt 过去分词: dealt 现在分词: dealing 第三人称单数: deals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('orphan', '[\'ɔːrfn]', 'n.孤儿 adj.孤儿的 vt.成孤儿', '1. The orphan was consigned to her uncle\'s care. 那孤儿托给她叔父照料。 2. The boy became an orphan at six. 那男孩六岁时成了孤儿。 3. Some orphan crops cannot be grown from seeds. 有些孤儿作物无法从种子生长起来。 4. The old lady took pity on the orphan kittens. 这老妇人觉得失去母猫的小猫可怜而把它们收容了下来。 5. She was orphaned at the age of ten. 她在十岁时成为孤儿。', '名词: orphanhood 过去式: orphaned 过去分词: orphaned 现在分词: orphaning 第三人称单数: orphans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hand', '[hænd]', 'n.手；协助；手艺 v.给；传 Hand. n.汉德（英文姓）', '1. It was written by hand. 这是手写的。 2. He has a book in one hand, and a pen in the other. 他一手拿书,一手拿笔。 3. Do you want a hand? 你需要帮忙吗？ 4. He\'s always willing to give a hand to anyone who asks. 任何人有求于他,他总是乐于帮助。 5. Please hand me that book. 请把那本书递给我。', '形容词: handless 名词: hander 过去式: handed 过去分词: handed 现在分词: handing 第三人称单数: hands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strife', '[straɪf]', 'n.争吵；冲突；倾轧；竞争', '1. She was faint with strife and dejected. 她被争吵弄得精疲力竭，情绪低落。 2. We really shouldn\'t intervene in their marital strife. 我们不该介入他们夫妻间的争吵。 3. The internecine strife was caused by a shortage of food. 这次内部冲突，是由于食物匮乏而引致的。 4. And he remains edgy about the continuing strife in Somalia. 梅莱斯也对索马里冲突不止而烦躁。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aboard', '[ə\'bɔːrd]', 'adv.在船上；在火车上；在飞机上 prep.上船；上飞机；上车', '1. Little Tom and the sailors spent two months aboard. 小汤姆和水手们在船上过了两个月。 2. All passengers aboard fell into the river. 船上所有乘客皆落入河中。 3. A limited menu is available aboard the train, but a nice bottle of vin rouge and a simple picnic hamper will enhance your Orient-Express fantasy. 在火车上提供的食物很有限，自备一瓶上好法国红葡萄酒和一份简单的野餐食盒，将会提升你东方快车之旅的乐趣。 4. The children were so excited to be taken aboard for the first time. 那些小孩第一次被带上飞机，简直兴奋极了。 5. They were the last two to go aboard the ship. 他们是最後两位上船的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rally', '[\'ræli]', 'n.集会；（价值等）回升；回合 vi.重整旗鼓；恢复精神；(人)集合起来 vt.嘲弄；重新召集；激励', '1. They will hold a peace rally. 他们要举行一个拥护和平的大会。 2. Countless people joined the rally at the square. 不计其数的人参加了广场上的集会。 3. After a brief rally share fall back to a new low. 股票经过一次短暂回升后回落到一个新的低点。 4. His sudden rally surprised the doctor. 他的突然复元使医生大为惊奇。 5. The team was thrown onto the defensive as their opponents rallied. 该队在对手重整旗鼓后,被迫采取守势。 6. The commander was able to rally the fleeing troops. 指挥官能够重整其溃散的部队。', '名词复数: rallies 过去式: rallied 过去分词: rallied 现在分词: rallying 第三人称单数: rallies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('paragraph', '[\'pærəɡræf]', 'n.段落；节 vt.将 ... 分段；写短评报道 vi.写短评', '1. The editor struck out the whole paragraph. 编辑把整段全删掉了。 2. You\'ll find the last paragraph extremely apropos. 你会觉得最后一段文字极为中肯。 3. Look at the second paragraph on page fifteen. 请看第十五页的第二段。 4. This point has been dealt with in the preceding paragraph. 这一点在前面一段里已经交代过了。 5. The student is ask to paragraph an essay in class. 学生们被要求在课堂上给一篇文章分段。 6. The editor asked him to paragraph. 编辑让他写短评。', '形容词: paragraphic 过去式: paragraphed 过去分词: paragraphed 现在分词: paragraphing 第三人称单数: paragraphs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discuss', '[dɪ\'skʌs]', 'v.讨论；论述；商量', '1. We will discuss the proposal at the meeting. 我们将在会议上讨论这项提议。 2. They said they had an important matter to discuss with you. 他们说有要事与你相商。 3. The causes of stress have already been discussed in Chapter 3. 压力产生的原因在第三章就已经论述过了。 4. We discussed when we should go. 我们商量什么时候动身。', '形容词: discussable 名词: discusser 过去式: discussed 过去分词: discussed 现在分词: discussing 第三人称单数: discusses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conservation', '[ˌkɑːnsər\'veɪʃn]', 'n.保存；保护；守恒；节约', '1. If I may refer back to the problem we discussed, I think we shall stress on the conservation of our natural resource. 请允许我重提我们刚才讨论过的问题，我想我们应该强调保存我们的自然资源。 2. Conservation methods will also help meet their energy needs. 能量保存方法也会有利于满足其能源需求。 3. Most people have come to accept the need for conservation of natural resources. 现在大多数人已认识到保护自然资源的必要。 4. Our community is a leader in the conservation of wildlife. 我们社区在野生动物保护方面走在前头。', '形容词: conservational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('curl', '[kɜːrl]', 'n.卷曲；卷发；年轮；漩涡；[足]曲线球 vt.弄卷；使弯曲 vi.变卷；弯曲', '1. As he got older, his hair lost its curl. 随着他渐渐长大,他的头发不再卷曲了。 2. The lovely boy has beautiful blonde curls. 这个可爱的小男孩长着漂亮的金黄色卷发。 3. He saw a curl on the water, the general forerunner of a storm at sea. 他看见水面有一个漩涡，这是大海风暴的常见前兆。 4. She doesn\'t curl her hair any longer. 她也不卷头发了。 5. The dying leaves became brown and curled up. 快死的叶子发黄而卷曲。', '过去式: curled 过去分词: curled 现在分词: curling 第三人称单数: curls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('data', '[\'deɪtə]', 'n.数据；资料 名词datum的复数形式.', '1. The data should be updated once a week. 这些数据应该每星期更新一次。 2. In Name, type a name for the data source. 在“名称”中,为数据源键入名称。 3. Very little data is available. 现有的资料十分不足。 4. The data is still being analyzed. 资料仍在分析中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('left', '[left]', 'adj.左边的 adv.向左 n.左边；左派分子；【体】左手拳 动词leave的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Do you always write left-handed? 你一向用左手写字吗? 2. He supports the left wing of the Labour Party. 他支持工党中的左翼. 3. As a result of a serious illness, she couldn\'t move her left leg. 患重病后,她的左腿不能动了。 4. Turn left here. 这里左转。 5. Britain cars are driven on the left. 在英国汽车靠左侧行驶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wait', '[weɪt]', 'v.等；等待 n.等待；等候', '1. She has impatience to wait for the bus. 她没有耐心等公共汽车到来。 2. He kept us waiting for ages while he packed his luggage. 他收拾行李，让我们等了好半天。 3. You will just have to wait your turn. 你得等到轮到你才行。 4. I don\'t like this long wait. 我不喜欢这种长时间的等待。', '过去式: waited 过去分词: waited 现在分词: waiting 第三人称单数: waits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ownership', '[\'oʊnərʃɪp]', 'n.所有权', '1. She disclaimed ownership of the vehicle. 她放弃了这辆车的所有权。 2. The ownership of the house is still unknown. 这栋房子的所有权至今无人知道。 3. The ownership of the land is disputed. 那土地的所有权有争议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('instrument', '[\'ɪnstrəmənt]', 'n.仪器；乐器；工具；器械 v.用器械（或仪器）装备；向…提交文书', '1. This instrument monitors the patient\'s heartbeats. 这台仪器监听病人的心跳。 2. He can play nearly every musical instrument. 他几乎能演奏每一件乐器。 3. A plough is an instrument used for farming. 犁是用于耕作的工具。 4. The hospital imported some surgical instruments. 医院进口了一些外科器械。', '过去式: instrumented 过去分词: instrumented 现在分词: instrumenting 第三人称单数: instruments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('union', '[\'juːniən]', 'n.结合；工会；联盟；和睦；连接轴；【数】并，并集 adj.联邦政府的；工会的', '1. They had a sound basis of union. 他们的结合有着坚实的基础。 2. He was elected the leader of the union. 他被选为工会的领导人。 3. He has changed his stance on monetary union. 他已经改变了对货币联盟的态度。 4. All the nationalities live together in perfect union. 各族人民非常和睦地生活在一起。 5. Nine States seceded from the Union government and established their own confederate government. 九个州脱离联邦政府,成立了自己的邦联政府。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hasty', '[\'heɪsti]', 'adj.匆匆的；轻率的；急忙的', '1. Some people are prone to jump to hasty conclusions. 有些人往往作出轻率的结论。', '副词: hastily 比较级: hastier 最高级: hastiest 名词: hastiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bubble', '[\'bʌbl]', 'n.气泡；泡影 v.起泡；冒泡；充满...感情', '1. A bubble will burst at the slightest touch. 气泡稍微一碰就破。 2. As a stock market bubble is taking shape, the investors should take precautions against the risks. 股市泡沫正在形成,投资者应该防范风险。 3. His hope vanished like a bubble. 他的希望化作泡影。 4. He didn\'t want to burst the newcomer\'s bubble. 他不想打破这个新来者的不切实际的美梦。 5. The water in the pan was beginning to bubble. 锅里的水开始起泡。', '过去式: bubbled 过去分词: bubbled 现在分词: bubbling 第三人称单数: bubbles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('describe', '[dɪ\'skraɪb]', 'vt.描述；说成；形容；画(尤指几何图形)', '1. The police asked me to describe exactly how it happened. 警察让我描述一下这事是怎样发生的。 2. Words cannot describe the beauty of the scene. 语言难以描述那景色之美丽。 3. He describes himself as a doctor. 他自称是医生。 4. No one could describe the scorn of her expression. 谁也无法形容她那股鄙夷万分的表情。', '形容词: describable 名词: describer 过去式: described 过去分词: described 现在分词: describing 第三人称单数: describes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('innocent', '[\'ɪnəsnt]', 'adj.清白的；无害的；无辜的；无知的；天真纯洁的', '1. A man is accounted innocent until he is proven guilty. 一个人未被证明有罪前，被视为是清白的。 2. He was charged with murder but found innocent later. 他被控杀人，但后来发现他是无罪的。 3. It was an innocent deception, meant as a joke. 那是个无伤大雅的骗术，开个玩笑而已。 4. He declared that he was innocent. 他声称自己是无罪的。', '副词: innocently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('column', '[\'kɑːləm]', 'n.栏；专栏；列；圆柱；柱；柱形物', '1. And in this column, you write down everything in the parcel. 在这一栏里,您要写上包裹里每一件东西。 2. He used to write a column for this newspaper. 他过去曾为这家报纸写专栏文章。 3. A blank column row is inserted. 此时,将插入一个空白列行。 4. The temple is supported by massive columns. 此庙由粗大的柱子支撑。', '形容词: columned');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('actual', '[\'æktʃuəl]', 'adj.实际的；事实上的', '1. The actual cause of the quake itself is the rupturing or breaking of rocks at or below the earth\'s surface. 地震本身的真正原因是地球表面的或地底下的岩石断裂或破裂。 2. We call the baby Doc. His actual name is Daniel. 我们把这个婴儿叫做多克,他的实际名字是丹尼尔。 3. I need the actual figures, not an estimate. 我需要确实的数字，不要估计的。 4. My calculation is based on notional figures, since the actual figures are not yet available. 因尚无实际数字，我是根据估计的数字计算的。', '副词: actually');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('leap', '[liːp]', 'v.跳跃；跃过；跃 n.跳跃；跃', '1. I leap for joy at the good news. 我一听到这个好消息高兴得跳了起来。 2. The thief leaped the wall and ran away. 小偷越墙逃跑了。 3. His name leapt out at me from the newspaper. 报纸上他的名字一下子跳入我的眼帘。 4. The boy took a leap from the window. 那个男孩从窗口跳下去。', '名词: leaper 过去式: leaped/leapt 过去分词: leaped/leapt 现在分词: leaping 第三人称单数: leaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('train', '[treɪn]', 'n.列车；火车；行列；一系列 vt.训练；培训；瞄准 vi.进行锻炼，接收训练；练习', '1. The 6:30 train for Berlin has been canceled. 6点30分开往柏林的列车已经取消。 2. I lost my train by three minutes. 我迟了3分钟，没赶上火车。 3. I saw a camel train. 我看到了一队的骆驼。 4. The telephone rang and interrupted my train of thought. 电话铃响了，打断了我的思路。 5. The challenger has been training hard for the big fight. 这位健将为参加拳击大赛夺魁而进行坚苦的锻炼。', '形容词: trainable 名词: trainability 过去式: trained 过去分词: trained 现在分词: training 第三人称单数: trains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ribbon', '[\'rɪbən]', 'n.缎带；带状物；色带 vt.用丝带装饰；撕碎', '1. She wears a ribbon belt round her waist. 她在腰部束了一条缎带。 2. She wore yellow ribbons in her hair. 她头发上戴着黄色缎带。 3. Ribbon hung from the bride\'s bouquet was tied in a bow. 从新娘的花束上垂下来的丝带打成了一个结。 4. I had to change the typewriter ribbon. 我不得不换掉打字机的色带。 5. We decorated our car lavishly,with ribbon. 我们花了一大笔钱用丝带装饰汽车。', '形容词: ribbony 过去式: ribboned 过去分词: ribboned 现在分词: ribboning 第三人称单数: ribbons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sensation', '[sen\'seɪʃn]', 'n.感觉；轰动；激动；知觉', '1. He had a sensation of dizziness. 他有一种晕眩的感觉。 2. I knew the train had stopped, but I had the sensation that it was moving backwards. 我知道火车已经停了，但我觉得火车在倒退。 3. The new discovery caused a great sensation. 这项新发现很轰动。 4. The outrageous book created a sensation. 那部耸人听闻的书曾轰动一时。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hobby', '[\'hɑːbi]', 'n.业余爱好', '1. His hobby is entomology. 他爱好昆虫学。 2. Angling is his main hobby. 钓鱼是他的主要爱好。 3. Some people like horseback ride, but I prefer golf as a hobby. 一些人喜欢马术，但是我宁愿把打高尔夫球作为一种业余爱好。 4. My hobby is a good safety-valve for the tension that builds up at work. 我用业余爱好来消除工作中产生的紧张情绪。', '名词: hobbyist 名词复数: hobbies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chain', '[tʃeɪn]', 'n.束缚；链条；链；(一)连串；连锁店（常用复数） vt.束缚；用铁链锁住', '1. Though you seek in garments the freedom of privacy you may find in them a harness and a chain. 你们想借着衣服得到隐私的自由,反而却因此为之羁绊和束缚。 2. She wore a silver chain around her neck. 她脖子上戴着一条银项链。 3. He detached a link from a chain. 他从链子上拆下一个链环。 4. The Government fear the strike may produce a chain reaction in other industries. 政府害怕罢工可能在其他行业产生连锁反应。 5. He is chained to his work. 他工作忙得不能分身。', '过去式: chained 过去分词: chained 现在分词: chaining 第三人称单数: chains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bind', '[baɪnd]', 'v.捆绑；装订；约束；强迫；团结 n.窘境', '1. She bound her hair with a handkerchief. 她用手绢把头发扎了起来。 2. This hint was hard enough to bind my hands. 这个暗示已经够使我束手无策了。 3. The publishing house decided to bind the new book in leather. 这家出版社决定用皮面装帧新书。 4. I am bound by my promise. 我必须遵守自己的诺言。 5. Their refusal to sign the contract has put us in a bit of a bind. 他们拒绝签约，从而使我们的处境有些困难。', '过去式: bound 过去分词: bound 现在分词: binding 第三人称单数: binds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dam', '[dæm]', 'n.水坝；堤；障碍物 v.筑坝；抑制(情感等）', '1. The dam was not strong enough to hold back the flood waters. 水坝不太坚固，挡不住洪水。 2. The village was swept away when the dam burst. 村庄在水坝决堤时被冲走了。 3. The water deepened after the dam was built. 堤坝建成后水已加深。 4. The river keeps rising and the dam is threatened. 河水不断上涨，大堤出现险情。 5. They are going to dam up the river to set up a hydropower station. 他们准备拦江筑坝建水电站。', '名词: dammer 过去式: dammed 过去分词: dammed 现在分词: damming 第三人称单数: dams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('leaflet', '[\'liːflət]', 'n.小叶；传单 v.散发传单', '1. Leaflet blades with scattered oil glands. 小叶叶片具星散的油腺体。 2. Leaflet blade abaxially with lateral vein axils yellowish crinite. 小叶叶片背面具侧脉腋淡黄具长软毛。 3. I rustle up a few helper to hand out leaflet. 我找到几个助手散发传单。 4. They distributed leaflets to customers. 他们给客户散发传单。 5. We were paid to leaflet the mall with advertisements. 有人雇佣我们在购物中心发放广告传单。', '过去式: leafleted/leafletted 过去分词: leafleted/leafletted 现在分词: leafleting/leafletting 第三人称单数: leaflets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('huge', '[hjuːdʒ]', 'adj.巨大的；庞大的；极大的', '1. The atomic explosion is always accompanied by huge fireball. 原子弹爆炸总是伴随着巨大的火球。 2. The huge ship was sunk by a homing missile. 这只巨大的军舰被一枚自动寻的导弹击中。 3. The destructive force of the storm is huge. 暴风雨的破坏力是巨大的。 4. He possesses a huge house on the hillside. 他在山上拥有一栋巨宅。', '副词: hugely 比较级: huger 最高级: hugest 名词: hugeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('themselves', '[ðəm\'selvz]', 'pron.他/她/它们自己；他/她/它们亲自；指性别不详的人时用以代替himself或herself himself/herself/itself的复数.', '1. They finished the work by themselves. 他们自己完成了这项工作。 2. They demand the right to govern themselves. 他们要求自治权。 3. They painted the house themselves. 他们亲自油漆了房屋。 4. They themselves made the decision. 他们自己做的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kill', '[kɪl]', 'v.杀死；终止；消灭；使痛苦；消磨；使精疲力竭 n.杀；猎获物', '1. His wife was killed in a car accident. 他的妻子在车祸中丧生。 2. They fumigated the room to kill the vermin. 他们用烟熏房间以杀死害虫。 3. The noise killed the music. 噪音淹没了音乐。 4. They have the right to kill a bill in Parliament . 他们有权使法案在国会不能通过。 5. The hunters are moving in for the kill. 猎手们正在围杀猎物。', '过去式: killed 过去分词: killed 现在分词: killing 第三人称单数: kills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eclipse', '[ɪ\'klɪps]', 'n.日或月食；丧失；没落 vt.形成日或月食；使 ... 黯然失色', '1. It will take an hour to reach full eclipse stage. 从月食到全食历时一个小时。 2. It was reported that there would be a lunar eclipse tomorrow evening. 据报道说，明天晚上有月食。 3. The moon is partly eclipsed. 月偏食了。 4. It was reported that there would be an annular eclipse tomorrow. 据报道说，明天有日环食。 5. Its economy may well eclipse Japan\'s in size in 20 years or so.\" 中国经济的规模在20年左右的时间里完全可能超过日本。', '过去式: eclipsed 过去分词: eclipsed 现在分词: eclipsing 第三人称单数: eclipses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('absolute', '[\'æbsəluːt]', 'adj.绝对的；确实的；专制的；完全的；独立的；无限制的 n.绝对的事物', '1. There is no absolute standard for beauty. 美是没有绝对的标准的。 2. Motion is absolute, while stillness is relative. 运动是绝对的，而静止是相对的。 3. There is no absolute freedom in the world. 世上没有绝对的自由。 4. The police have absolute proof of his guilt. 警方有他犯罪的确凿证据。', '名词: absoluteness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anguish', '[\'æŋɡwɪʃ]', 'n.苦闷；痛苦 v.（使）极苦闷；（使）极痛苦', '1. Physical disability causes mental anguish. 生理伤残会引起心理苦闷。 2. I expected something with a terrible anguish that tortured my heart. 在极度揪心的苦闷中我似乎在期待着某种东西。 3. The quarrel caused her great anguish. 争吵给她造成了极大的痛苦。 4. Her mental anguish was beyond words. 她内心的痛苦难以用言语形容。 5. Physical disability causes mental anguish. 生理伤残会引起心理苦闷。', '过去式: anguished 过去分词: anguished 现在分词: anguishing 第三人称单数: anguishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spontaneous', '[spɑːn\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.自发的，自然的，本能的；自然产生的', '1. He is spontaneous to offer help. 他主动提供帮助。 2. It is a spontaneous cheer from the crowd. 那是群众自发的喝彩。 3. The spontaneous applause cut the singer short. 自发的掌声打断了歌唱家的演唱。 4. The eruption of volcanoes is spontaneous. 火山爆发是自然产生的。', '副词: spontaneously 名词: spontaneousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('argue', '[\'ɑːrɡjuː]', 'v.说服；争论；辩论', '1. We argued her into joining us. 我们说服她参加了宴会。 2. The United States should, he argues, attempt to remain aloof. 他认为，美国应保持超然态度。 3. As we\'ve seen, the experts argue about which diet is best. 正如我们所看见,而专家们争论,是最好的饮食。 4. One student make so bold as to argue with the professor 有个学生真冒失, 竟然和教授争论起来', '名词: arguer 过去式: argued 过去分词: argued 现在分词: arguing 第三人称单数: argues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tell', '[tel]', 'v.告诉；吩咐；讲述；表达；辨别；判断；泄露；告发；产生效果', '1. It\'s very kind of you to tell me the truth. 你真好,告诉我这真相。 2. Let me tell you some details about clearance. 让我告诉你一些通关的细节。 3. Tell that joker to stop using my parking space. 叫那个家伙不要占用我的停车场。 4. He always does what his superiors tell him. 他惟上级之命是从。', '形容词: tellable 过去式: told 过去分词: told 现在分词: telling 第三人称单数: tells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('physiological', '[ˌfɪziə\'lɒdʒɪkl]', 'adj.生理的；生理学的', '1. The physiological needs are reasonably satisfied. 生理的需要得到合理的满足。 2. Objective To Study the effect of Haematococcus pluvialis powder on physiological metabolism of Wistar rats. 目的观察红球藻粉对大鼠生理的影响。 3. Certain species of aquatic animals are capable of producing physiological shocks. 某些种类的水生生物能够引起生理学的电击。 4. From a physiological standpoint \"health\"refers to a persons quality of health and their ability to adapt to the outer world. 从生理学的角度来看，体质是指人的健康水平和对外界的适应能力。', '副词: physiologically 异体字: physiologic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('live', '[lɪv]', 'v.活着；居住；过着 adj.活的；直播的；现场的；带电的；燃烧着的；当前的 adv.现场', '1. People cannot live without air. 没有空气，人们就不能生存。 2. After she died he had nothing to live for. 她去世后,他便没有了生活目标。 3. He\'s a tramp and used to living rough. 他是流浪汉,惯于风餐雨卧。 4. Where do you live? 你住在哪儿？ 5. The cat is playing with a live mouse. 猫在戏弄那只活老鼠。 6. The landing on the moon was telecast live. 现场转播了登月行动。', '名词: liveness 过去式: lived 过去分词: lived 现在分词: living 第三人称单数: lives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('representative', '[ˌreprɪ\'zentətɪv]', 'n.代表；众议员；典型 adj.代表的；典型的；代表制的', '1. That representative brought forth an amendment to the press law. 那位代表提出了一项对新闻法的修正案。 2. A senator takes precedence over a Representative. 参议员的地位高于众议员。 3. The tiger is a representative of the cat family. 老虎是猫科动物的典型。 4. Are your opinions representative of the other students? 你的意见是否代表其他学生的意见？', '副词: representatively 名词: representativeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('parent', '[\'perənt]', 'n.父母；根源 v.抚养；产生', '1. My parents have gone to Hangzhou for holiday. 我父母已经去杭州度假了。 2. Being a parent can be hard work. 当父母可是件辛苦的事。 3. Ignorance is the parent of many evils. 无知是许多罪恶的根源。 4. Greed is the parent of many evils. 贪婪是万恶之根源。 5. We should parent children with both love and discipline. 我们应该用爱和管教来抚养孩子。', '名词: parenthood 过去式: parented 过去分词: parented 现在分词: parenting 第三人称单数: parents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('liberate', '[\'lɪbəreɪt]', 'v.解放；使获得自由；释出；放出', '1. The country was liberated in 1966. 这个国家是在1966年解放的。 2. Our army had liberated many occupied areas. 我们的军队解放了许多地区。 3. This small software can liberate your fingers! 这个小软件可以解放你的手指啦！ 4. They can liberate us from the limitations of our thoughts and feelings. 他们可以使我们从思想与感受解放。', '副词: liberatingly 名词: liberator 过去式: liberated 过去分词: liberated 现在分词: liberating 第三人称单数: liberates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cottage', '[\'kɑːtɪdʒ]', 'n.小屋；村舍', '1. The cottage could accommodate up to five people. 这间小屋最多能容纳5个人。 2. The cottage was a casualty of the forest fire. 那小屋被森林大火烧毁。 3. His cottage is on the gentle slope of the hill. 他的小屋在山的缓坡上。 4. He has a house in London and a cottage near the sea. 他在伦敦有一所房子，在海边还有一个小屋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('corporation', '[ˌkɔːrpə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.公司；法人', '1. He works for a large American corporation. 他为美国一家大型公司工作。 2. Several new members have come into this corporation. 这个公司又有新人员加入。 3. The British Broadcasting Corporation is very famous across the world. 英国广播公司在世界上很出名。 4. West Coast Corps is a large corporation. 西海岸公司是个大型公司。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shadow', '[\'ʃædoʊ]', 'n.影子；阴影；阴暗；荫；暗处 vt.投阴影于；跟踪；预示 vi.渐变；变阴暗 adj.影子内阁的；阴影的', '1. The tree cast its shadow on the wall. 树影映在墙上。 2. His shadow followed him along the road. 他的影子一路上跟着他。 3. The scandal cast a shadow on his career. 这件丑闻给他的事业投上了一层阴影。 4. Sometimes she sits alone in the shadow. 有时候她独自一人坐在幽暗处。 5. Figmentary fears can shadow our whole existence. 想像中的恐惧能使我们整个生活蒙上阴影。 6. Any pregnant woman who paed through her shadow would miscarry. 穿过她的阴影的所有孕妇会失败。', '名词: shadower 过去式: shadowed 过去分词: shadowed 现在分词: shadowing 第三人称单数: shadows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('careful', '[\'kerfl]', 'adj.小心谨慎的；慎重的；精心的', '1. He is careful in his speech. 他说话谨慎。 2. Be careful in dealing with such people. 与这种人打交道要小心谨慎。 3. You should be more careful with your money. 你花钱要慎重一些。 4. After careful consideration, we\'ve decided to accept their offer. 经过慎重的考虑，我们决定接受他们的提议。', '副词: carefully 名词: carefulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aware', '[ə\'wer]', 'adj.知道的；意识到的', '1. If you were aware of all that, you would change your mind. 如果你知道了那一切,你会改变主意的。 2. Then he became aware that they were regarding him with interest. 这时,他意识到他们都在饶有兴趣地看着他。', '名词: awareness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('combine', '[kəm\'baɪn]', 'v.联合；使结合；结合 n.集团；联合收割机；联合企业', '1. Two parties will combine to defeat the third. 两党派将联合以击败第三党。 2. We can\'t always combine work with pleasure. 我们并不总是能在工作中享受到乐趣。 3. He combines creative imagination and true scholarship. 他同时具有创造性想象力和真正的治学谨严学风。 4. We should combine work with rest. 我们应劳逸结合。 5. The newspaper combine threatened all the smaller papers. 这家报刊集团威胁者小报社的生存。', '名词: combiner 过去式: combined 过去分词: combined 现在分词: combining 第三人称单数: combines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('additional', '[ə\'dɪʃənl]', 'adj.附加的；额外的', '1. He had to pay some additional charges. 他不得不付些附加费。 2. Additional material is overprinted in red. 附加材料是用红色加印上的。 3. You should know the additional responsibilities that are incidental to the job. 你该知道做这项工作要承担额外责任。 4. We are willing to pay an additional fee for immediate delivery . 我们愿意为即期交货支付一笔额外的费用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accumulate', '[ə\'kjuːmjəleɪt]', 'v.积累；增加；聚集', '1. They set out to accumulate a huge mass of data. 他们开始积累大量的资料。 2. Dust and dirt soon accumulates if a house is not cleaned regularly. 房屋不经常打扫,尘土很快就越积越多。 3. True poetry accumulates meaning every time it is read. 真正好诗愈念涵义愈丰富。 4. However, as the evidence began to accumulate, experts from the zoo felt obliged to investigate. 然而，当证据日趋增多时，该动物园的专家们感到有必要进行调查。', '形容词: accumulable 过去式: accumulated 过去分词: accumulated 现在分词: accumulating 第三人称单数: accumulates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('estimate', '[\'estɪmət]', 'n.估价；估计 v.估计；估价；评价', '1. This is an outside estimate of the price. 这是最高的估价。 2. Your estimate was rejected by the seller. 你的估价单被卖家回绝了。 3. This is a safe estimate. 这是个有把握的估计。 4. We need to make an accurate estimate beforehand. 我们需要事先作出准确的估计。 5. I estimate it will take three months to build the bridge . 我估计建造这座桥得用3个月时间。', '形容词: estimative 名词: estimator 过去式: estimated 过去分词: estimated 现在分词: estimating 第三人称单数: estimates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('squirrel', '[\'skwɜːrəl]', 'n.松鼠；松鼠皮毛 vt.储存', '1. The squirrel is a lovely small animal. 松鼠是一种可爱的小动物。 2. The squirrel ran up a tree and got out of my reach. 松鼠跑到树上去了，我逮不着。 3. The squirrel hoards up nuts for the winter. 松鼠储藏坚果以防冬天。 4. Nervous householders continue to squirrel more money away in the banks. 不安的居民持续不断地把更多钱存入银行里。', '过去式: squirreled/squirrelled 过去分词: squirreled/squirrelled 现在分词: squirreling/squirrelling 第三人称单数: squirrels/squirrels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('king', '[kɪŋ]', 'n.国王；（纸牌）老K adj.王的；重要的；基本的 v.成为国王 King. n.金（姓氏）；上帝；耶稣', '1. The lion is called the king of beasts. 狮子号称百兽之王。 2. The king is the most important person in a kingdom. 国王是一个王国中最重要的人物。 3. You can also get a glimpse of the King of All Teas. 还可以一睹茶中之王的风采。 4. So the servants of king Hezekiah came to Isaiah. 希西家王的臣仆就来到以赛亚那里。 5. The black horse is one of Mr. King\'s stable. 那匹黑马是金先生的赛马之一。', '过去式: kinged 过去分词: kinged 现在分词: kinging 第三人称单数: kings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rage', '[reɪdʒ]', 'n.狂怒；大怒；狂暴；肆虐；风行 v.大怒；怒斥；激烈进行；肆虐', '1. He was mad with rage. 他快要气疯了。 2. I was gnashing my teeth with rage. 我咬牙切齿愤怒已极。 3. He flew into a rage at the news. 他听到这个消息勃然大怒。 4. The storm showed elemental rage in its violence. 这场风暴显示了大自然的狂暴力量。 5. You are not yourself when you rage like that. 你那样大发雷霆有点失常。', '过去式: raged 过去分词: raged 现在分词: raging 第三人称单数: rages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contest', '[\'kɑːntest]', 'n.竞赛；比赛 vt.驳斥；争取 vi.奋斗', '1. She won a gold medal for her fine performance in the contest. 她在竞赛中成绩优异获金牌。 2. This football match is an unequal contest. 这场足球赛是一场实力悬殊的比赛。 3. Janet said she is thinking about attending a KTV contest. 珍妮说她正考虑参加一个KTV歌唱比赛。 4. I intend to contest the judge\'s decision in another court. 我准备下次开庭时反驳法官的判决。', '形容词: contestable 名词: contestation 过去式: contested 过去分词: contested 现在分词: contesting 第三人称单数: contests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('absorb', '[əb\'sɔːrb]', 'vt.吸收；吸引 ... 的注意；吞并；承受', '1. Dry sand absorbs water. 干沙吸收水份。 2. Did you absorb everything the professor said? 教授说的你全部理解了吗? 3. His business absorbs him. 他的业务使他全神贯注。 4. Large nations shouldn\'t absorb smaller ones. 大国不应当吞并小国。', '形容词: absorbable 副词: absorbingly 名词: absorbability 过去式: absorbed 过去分词: absorbed 现在分词: absorbing 第三人称单数: absorbs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('support', '[sə\'pɔːrt]', 'vt.支持；承受；支撑；供养；资助；证实；支援；担任演出嘉宾 n.支持；支撑；援助；供养；依据；助演嘉宾', '1. The lawyer cite a previous case to support his argument. 律师引用了以前的案例来支持他的论点。 2. Will you use your influence to prevail upon them to support the suggestion? 你能不能利用你的影响劝他们支持这个建议呢? 3. The pillars support the weight of the roof. 这些柱子支撑着屋顶的重量。 4. Is this bridge strong enough to support heavy lorries? 这座桥禁得住重型卡车通行吗? 5. She spoke in support of the project. 她发言支持这项计划。', '过去式: supported 过去分词: supported 现在分词: supporting 第三人称单数: supports');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('telescope', '[\'telɪskoʊp]', 'n.望远镜 v.缩短；压缩；套叠', '1. He saw a hungry wolf on the prowl with his telescope. 他通过望远镜看到了一头四处觅食的饿狼。 2. What is the range of this telescope? 这架望远镜的有效距离多大? 3. He was too poor to buy an astronomical telescope. 他太穷了，买不起天文望远镜。 4. I suggest we telescope the seminar into an hour. 我建议将研讨会缩短为一个小时。', '过去式: telescoped 过去分词: telescoped 现在分词: telescoping 第三人称单数: telescopes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tea', '[tiː]', 'n.茶；茶叶；茶树；茶点', '1. A nice cup of tea will soothe your nerves. 一杯好茶可以使你的心绪平静下来。 2. I\'d like to place an order for some tea with you. 我想从贵公司订购一些茶叶。 3. Tea plants grow well on the fertile mountain land. 茶树在这片肥沃的山地上长得很好。 4. They were regaled with tea and cakes. 他们被飨以茶点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extravagant', '[ɪk\'strævəɡənt]', 'adj.奢侈的；浪费的；过度的；大量的', '1. She\'s got very extravagant tastes. 她有很奢侈的嗜好。 2. Extravagant people never save money. 奢侈的人攒不下钱。 3. The millionaire talked cold turkey to his extravagant nephew, hinting that he might be disinherited. 那百万富翁对他挥霍无度的侄儿晓以利害，并暗示其继承权可能被剥夺。 4. She was pilloried in the press for her extravagant parties. 她的聚会十分铺张，新闻界对她大加嘲弄。', '副词: extravagantly 名词: extravagantness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prescription', '[prɪ\'skrɪpʃn]', 'n.处方；药方；对策', '1. The doctor is writing a prescription. 医生正在开处方。 2. The doctor dispensed a prescription to his patient. 医生开处方给病人配药。 3. The prescription of drugs is a doctor\'s responsibility. 开药方是医生的职责。 4. His prescription for economic recovery was not well received. 他为经济复苏提出的对策反应不佳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('construct', '[kən\'strʌkt]', 'vt.建造；构筑；造(句) n.构想', '1. This factory was constructed by our company. 这家工厂是由我们公司建设的。 2. They are planning to construct a new supermarket. 他们正在计划建造一个新的超级市场。 3. You must learn how to construct a logical argument. 你必须学会怎样确立合乎逻辑的论点。 4. He taught us how to construct sentences. 他教我们怎样造句。 5. There is a contrast between lived reality and the construct held in the mind. 现实生活与头脑所持概念之间有明显差别。', '形容词: constructible 名词: constructor 过去式: constructed 过去分词: constructed 现在分词: constructing 第三人称单数: constructs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('universal', '[ˌjuːnɪ\'vɜːrsl]', 'adj.普遍的；全世界的；宇宙的；全体的；通用的 n.通用原理，普遍原则', '1. These phenomena is very universal. 这些现象己经非常普遍了。 2. Overpopulation is a universal problem. 人口过多是全球性的问题。 3. Music has been called the universal language. 人们称音乐为世界的语言。 4. The doer is a universal structure. 行事者是一个宇宙的结构。 5. There are no economic universals. 英语是一种世界通用的语言。', '副词: universally 名词: universalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elite', '[eɪ\'liːt]', 'n.精英 adj.精英的；优秀的', '1. The elite are the competitive focus of 21 century. 精英人才是21世纪国际间竞争的焦点。 2. It is a luxury brand established for the elite and the affluent. 这是一个为精英群体和富人所创设的奢侈品牌。 3. It is indubitable that he is an elite in information technology. 毫无疑问，他是信息技术界的精英。 4. Public opinion is influenced by the small elite who control the media. 舆论为少数控制着新闻媒介的上层人士所左右。 5. This is an elite group reserved for members only. 这是仅为会员保留的精英小组。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cherish', '[\'tʃerɪʃ]', 'vt.珍爱；抱有；抚育', '1. Life is hope, so we should cherish life. 生命就是希望 2. I cherish my independence. 我很珍惜我的自由。 3. I cherish the memory of those happy times. 我把那些美好的时光珍藏在自己的记忆里。 4. A mother cherishes her baby. 母亲疼爱孩子。', '副词: cherishingly 名词: cherisher 过去式: cherished 过去分词: cherished 现在分词: cherishing 第三人称单数: cherishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bulletin', '[\'bʊlətɪn]', 'n.公报；期刊；新闻快报；公示 vt.发表；用公告通知', '1. The mid-day bulletin had not mentioned any definite area. 中午的公报没说具体的地点。 2. Here is a letter adapted from DEAR ABBY, Philadelphia Bulletin, March9,1973. 这里摘登一封＇亲爱的爱毕＇的回信，刊登在一九七三年三月九日的＇费城公报＇上。 3. I finally bought the Bulletin of Ordnance Information. 我终于买到了《兵器情报通报》(期刊)。 4. The radio bulletin warned of the typhoon. 收音机新闻快报发布了台风警报。 5. The company bulletined the staff to attend the meeting. 公司用公告通知全体员工参加会议。', '过去式: bulletined 过去分词: bulletined 现在分词: bulletining 第三人称单数: bulletins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('underground', '[ˌʌndə\'ɡraʊnd]', 'adj.地下的；秘密的 adv.在地下；秘密地 n.地下；地铁；地道；秘密活动', '1. Listen to the Sound From Underground. 听听地下的声音。 2. Underground water that is held in the soil and in pervious rocks. 土壤和能渗透的岩石中含有的地下的水。 3. He is well known for his reports on underground crime and gangs. 他因为关于报道秘密的犯罪和帮派而出名。 4. The insurrectionary detachments started in Yunghsin as an underground force,but they have come into the open since we captured the entire county. 暴动队始于永新，原是秘密的，夺取全县以后，公开了。 5. Moles stay underground most of the time. 钱鼠大部分时间住在地下。 6. Moles stay underground most of the time. 钱鼠大部分时间住在地下。', '过去式: undergrounded 过去分词: undergrounded 现在分词: undergrounding 第三人称单数: undergrounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('simulate', '[\'sɪmjuleɪt]', 'vt.假装；模拟；模仿', '1. These insects can simulate dead leaves . 这些昆虫可以伪装成枯叶。 2. I tried to simulate surprise at the news. 听到这个消息后，我竭力装出一副吃惊的样子。 3. He shook a sheet of metal to simulate the noise of thunder. 他摇动一块金属薄片来模拟雷声。 4. You can simulate different browser types for tests. 您可以为测试模拟不同类型的浏览器。', '形容词: simulative 过去式: simulated 过去分词: simulated 现在分词: simulating 第三人称单数: simulates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trousers', '[\'traʊzərz]', 'n.裤子', '1. Flared trousers are out this year. 今年喇叭裤不时兴了。 2. The boy\'s trousers need a patch on the knee. 这孩子的裤子膝盖上需要打个补丁。 3. He tucked his shirt into his trousers. 他把衬衫下摆塞入裤中。 4. This pair of trousers is too tight for me. 这条裤子我穿太紧了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rainbow', '[\'reɪnboʊ]', 'n.彩虹；五彩缤纷的排列；幻想', '1. Do you see rainbow? 你看到彩虹了吗？ 2. A rainbow is usually seen after a heavy rain. 大雨之后常有彩虹。 3. Now we can bask in the rainbow of the memories that we\'ll nurture in the years ahead. 在未来岁月里，让我们在记忆的长虹里永远珍藏对他的怀念。 4. We saw a beautiful rainbow across the sky. 我们看到了一条五彩缤纷的虹横贯天空。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pillar', '[\'pɪlər]', 'n.柱子；支柱；核心(人物) vt.用柱支持', '1. The robber tied him to a pillar. 强盗把他捆在柱子上。 2. A creeper was entwined round the pillar. 一根攀缘植物缠绕在柱子上。 3. The enemy was hurried from pillar to post. 敌人被赶得东逃西窜走投无路。 4. The textile industry is a traditional pillar industry in China. 纺织工业是中国传统的支柱产业。', '过去式: pillared 过去分词: pillared 现在分词: pillaring 第三人称单数: pillars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('engage', '[ɪn\'ɡeɪdʒ]', 'v.雇佣；啮合；与……交战；答应；订婚；预定；参加；从事', '1. The restaurant decide to engage a pop singer. 餐馆决定雇用一名流行歌手。 2. If the big gear did not engage with the small one,the machine would refuse to work. 如果大齿轮与小齿轮不相啮合的话，机器就不会工作。 3. Our orders are to engage (the enemy) immediately. 我们的命令是立即(与敌军)开战。 4. I will engage to manage the business if you will engage to provide the capital. 如果你答应出资本，我答应经管这个生意。', '名词: engager 过去式: engaged 过去分词: engaged 现在分词: engaging 第三人称单数: engages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nominal', '[\'nɑːmɪnl]', 'adj.名义上的；象征性的；名词性的 n.名词词组', '1. He is only the nominal head of the country. 他只是那个国家名义上的元首。 2. He remained in nominal control of the business for another ten years. 他名义上又掌管了这家公司十年。 3. She charged only a nominal fee for her work. 她为所做的工作只收取象征性的费用。 4. Such a nominal phrase mainly acts as the subject or object in a sentence. 这样的名词性词组在句子中主要充当主语和宾语。', '副词: nominally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('productive', '[prə\'dʌktɪv]', 'adj.生产的；有成效的；多产的', '1. Their productive cycle covers several decades. 它们的生产周期可延续几十年。 2. Our productive task is making the machine. 我们的生产任务是造机器。 3. They work hard, but their efforts are not very productive. 他们很努力，但效率不太高。 4. I spent a very productive hour in the library. 我在图书馆里的这一小时收获很大。', '副词: productively 名词: productiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('metaphor', '[\'metəfər]', 'n.象征；隐喻', '1. In poetry the rose is often a metaphor for love. 玫瑰在诗中通常作为爱的象征。 2. She has a striking originality in her use of metaphor. 她在运用隐喻方面有独创性。 3. This metaphor is beyond (above) all comprehension. 这个隐喻难以理解。 4. Then you only need to learn one metaphor. 然后你只需要学习一个隐喻。', '形容词: metaphoric 副词: metaphorically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discern', '[dɪ\'sɜːrn]', 'v.辨别；看出；察觉', '1. Sometimes it\'s not easy to discern between the true and the false. 有时辨别真伪并不容易。 2. He was just able to discern the road in the dark. 他在黑暗中勉强能辨出道路。 3. They can discern me in spite of the fog. 虽然有雾，但他们能认得出我。 4. I soon discerned that the man was lying. 我马上察觉出那人在撒谎。', '名词: discerner 过去式: discerned 过去分词: discerned 现在分词: discerning 第三人称单数: discerns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('integrate', '[\'ɪntɪɡreɪt]', 'v.整合；结合；取消隔离；求积分 adj.完整的；组合的', '1. The Message Board tool is an easy tool to integrate into daily school life. 留言板是一种非常方便的工具,可以将其整合到日常学校生活中。 2. Only 20% of teachers report feeling very well prepared to integrate education technology into classroom instruction. 仅有20%25的教师认为他们感觉能够将技术与课堂教学进行整合。 3. I learn quickly. I integrate disparate concepts with relative ease. 我学习速度很快,我能将完全不同的概念毫不费力地结合在一起。 4. We must carry out the Party\'s education policy that education should serve socialist modernization and the people and integrate itself with productive labor and social practice. 全面贯彻党的教育方针 5. Science is not an independent knowledge system, it has to integrate from various perspectives in order to reach a full understanding. 但是科学并非独立的知识系统，必须从不同的角度作综合性研究，方能对它有较完整的认识。', '形容词: integrative 过去式: integrated 过去分词: integrated 现在分词: integrating 第三人称单数: integrates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suspend', '[sə\'spend]', 'v.暂停；悬浮；中止；勒令停职', '1. As the workers went on strike, the company was obliged to suspend its operations. 由于工人罢工,该公司被迫暂停营运。 2. Such fine particles suspend readily in water. 这种微粒极易悬浮在水中。 3. They decided to suspend trade with that country. 他们决定中断和那个国家的贸易。 4. The policeman was suspended while the complaint was investigated. 因该警察遭投诉，在调查期间已令其暂停职务。', '过去式: suspended 过去分词: suspended 现在分词: suspending 第三人称单数: suspends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grade', '[ɡreɪd]', 'n.等级；年级；成绩；斜坡 v.分级；评分；渐次变化', '1. This grade of wool can be sold at a fairly low price. 这种等级的羊毛只能以相当低的价格卖出。 2. He\'s not in the first grade as a musician. 他不是第一流的音乐家。 3. He is in the third grade. 他读三年级。 4. He received a failing grade on the term paper. 他的期末报告不及格。 5. They grade eggs before they send them to the shops. 他们先把鸡蛋分等再送往商店。', '过去式: graded 过去分词: graded 现在分词: grading 第三人称单数: grades');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cup', '[kʌp]', 'n.杯子；一杯之量；奖杯；罩杯 vt.使成杯形；把某物放入杯中', '1. This cup is made of stainless steel. 这只杯子是不锈钢做的。 2. Please fill the cup with water. 请把这个杯子装满水。 3. Would you like a cup of tea? 你想喝杯茶吗？ 4. Eight horses will race for the cup. 将有八匹马参赛争夺奖杯。 5. When we want to hear something more clearly we cup our hands behind our ears. 我们想听得更清晰一些时，就把双手弯成杯状放在耳后。', '过去式: cupped 过去分词: cupped 现在分词: cupping 第三人称单数: cups');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('waist', '[weɪst]', 'n.腰部；腰', '1. Her hair nearly reached down to her waist. 她的头发几乎垂到了腰部。 2. She wears a ribbon belt round her waist. 她在腰部束了一条缎带。 3. If the skirt is too big, we can take in the waist. 要是裙子太大了，我们可以把腰部收紧一些。 4. He put his arm around her waist. 他搂住了她的腰。', '形容词: waistless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attorney', '[ə\'tɜːrni]', 'n.(辩护)律师', '1. He became a prominent attorney. 他成了有名的律师。 2. His uncle obtained an attorney for him. 他的叔叔为他请了律师。 3. The attorney is working in a divorce case. 律师正忙于一个离婚案件。', '名词: attorneyship 名词复数: attorneys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('situated', '[\'sɪtʃueɪtɪd]', 'adj.位于；处于 ...境地的 动词situate的过去式和过去分词', '1. The school is situated just outside the town. 学校就位于镇子的外面。 2. Most of China is situated in the temperate zone. 中国大部分地区处于温带。 3. The corporation is rather awkwardly situated. 公司处境相当尴尬。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('submit', '[səb\'mɪt]', 'vt.使服从；使屈服；提交；递交；认为 vi.屈从', '1. We will submit ourselves to the court\'s judgement. 我们服从法庭的判决。 2. We have to submit ourselves to discipline. 我们必须遵守纪律。 3. He submitted his proposal for urban development to the city council. 他将城市发展建议提交市议会。 4. Please fill in and submit the form below. 请填写并递交以下表格。 5. They refused to submit to the unjust decision. 他们拒绝服从这个不公正的决定。', '名词: submittal 过去式: submitted 过去分词: submitted 现在分词: submitting 第三人称单数: submits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('witness', '[\'wɪtnəs]', 'n.目击者；证人 vt.目击；经历；见证；出席；观察 vi.证明；为(宗教信仰)做见证', '1. The witness was telling about the whole accident. 目击者正在讲述整个事故的过程。 2. The lawyer examined the witness. 律师讯问了证人。 3. A material witness failed to appear in court. 一名重要的证人没有出庭。 4. Did anyone witness the traffic accident? 有谁目击了这场交通事故？ 5. The empty cupboard was a witness of his poverty. 空的食橱就是他贫穷的证明。', '名词: witnesser 过去式: witnessed 过去分词: witnessed 现在分词: witnessing 第三人称单数: witnesses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dine', '[daɪn]', 'v.用正餐；进餐', '1. She told me she would have to dine with Helen that night. 她告诉我那夜她必须与海伦一起进餐。 2. Every weekend, we dine at a nice little restaurant in the neighbourhood. 每个周末，我们在附近一家别致的小餐馆进餐。', '过去式: dined 过去分词: dined 现在分词: dining 第三人称单数: dines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('operate', '[\'ɑːpəreɪt]', 'v.操作；运转；经营；动手术', '1. It\'s too difficult for him to operate this new sophisticated machine. 对他来说,操作这台复杂的机器太难了。 2. The lift doesn\'t operate properly. 这台电梯运转不正常。 3. They operate three factories and a huge warehouse. 他们经营三家工厂和一个大仓库。 4. A large number of factories operate in the red. 许多工厂都是负债经营。', '过去式: operated 过去分词: operated 现在分词: operating 第三人称单数: operates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fluent', '[\'fluːənt]', 'adj.流利的；流畅的', '1. She speaks fluent and idiomatic French. 她说得一口又流利又地道的法语。 2. She likes him all the better for his fluent spoken English. 正因为他操一口流利的英语，她更爱他。 3. His work is rather fluent and felicitous. 他的作品十分流畅，措辞巧妙。 4. Her fluent movements surprised us. 她那协调优美的动作让我们惊奇。', '副词: fluently 名词: fluency');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prompt', '[prɑːmpt]', 'adj.迅速的；敏捷的；立刻的 vt.激起；促进；推动；提示 vi.提示 n.提示；提示的内容 n.[商]付款期限', '1. The occasion calls for prompt action. 这场合需要迅速的行动。 2. Their prompt actions prevented the fire from spreading. 他们敏捷的行动阻止了火势的蔓延。 3. Thank you for your prompt reply to our telegram. 多谢您对我们电报的即刻答复。 4. His curiosity prompted him to ask questions . 他的好奇心激起他问许多问题。 5. Will you prompt for us at the next performance? 下场演出时你给我们提词好吗? 6. The speaker was rather hesitant and had to be given a frequent prompt by the chairman. 那个发言人讲话结结巴巴的,经常得由主席给个提示。', '副词: promptly 比较级: prompter 最高级: promptest 名词: prompter 过去式: prompted 过去分词: prompted 现在分词: prompting 第三人称单数: prompts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('marble', '[\'mɑːrbl]', 'n.大理石；弹子，弹珠 vt.使有大理石的花纹', '1. This table is made of marble. 这个桌子是大理石的。 2. Michelangelo carved in marble. 米开朗琪罗在大理石上雕刻。 3. There are many perpendicular marble columns in Greek temples. 希腊庙宇有很多垂直的大理石柱。 4. My little son has many marbles. 我的小儿子有许多弹珠。', '形容词: marbly 过去式: marbled 过去分词: marbled 现在分词: marbling 第三人称单数: marbles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guide', '[ɡaɪd]', 'n.向导；导游；指南；指导者 vt.指导；引导；为 ... 领路 vi.作导游', '1. I know the place well, so let me be your guide. 我熟悉那地方 2. As a university graduate, I am seeking a job as a tourist guide. 作为一名大学毕业生,我正在谋求一份当导游的工作。 3. These philosophical views serve as a guide in life. 这些哲学观点可以作为处世指南。 4. His elder sister had been his guide, counsellor and friend. 他姐姐过去一直指导他，给他出主意，是他的朋友。 5. His entire life was guided by his religious beliefs. 他的宗教信仰指导了他的整个人生。', '形容词: guidable 名词: guider 过去式: guided 过去分词: guided 现在分词: guiding 第三人称单数: guides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conductor', '[kən\'dʌktər]', 'n.售票员；导体；指挥', '1. The conductor punched his bus ticket. 售票员用剪票夹在他的汽车票上打孔。 2. She knows why the metal is the good conductor. 她知道金属为什么是好的导体。 3. Rubber is not a conductor, and neither is plastics. 橡胶不是导体，塑料也不是导体。 4. With his baton the conductor was beating time. 指挥用指挥棒打着拍节。', '形容词: conductorial 名词: conductorship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tourist', '[\'tʊrɪst]', 'n.旅游者；二等舱 adj.观光的；乘坐二等舱的', '1. The tourist complained that the room was too dirty. 游客抱怨说房间太脏了。 2. The tourist is a Hungarian. 这名游客是匈牙利人。 3. London is full of tourists in the summer. 夏季伦敦有很多游客。 4. A rd class is a tourist class. 三等舱就是一般游客用的舱座。 5. We bought a tourist handbook before going travelling. 出去旅游前,我们先买了一本旅游指南。', '形容词: touristic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cattle', '[\'kætl]', 'n.牛；家畜；畜牲', '1. There is much forage for the cattle. 那儿有很多喂牛的饲料。 2. There are many herds of cattle in the meadow. 牧场上有许多牛群。 3. Clover can be grown as food for cattle. 苜蓿可以用作牛饲料。 4. He lives on a farm, so he knows a lot about cattle. 他住在农场，所以对家畜知之甚多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shady', '[\'ʃeɪdi]', 'adj.荫凉的；可疑的', '1. The arbor provided a shady resting place in the park. 公园里的凉亭提供了一个荫凉的休息处。 2. He went outside the walls, sat under a shady plant and sulked. 他走到围墙外面，站在一棵荫凉的植物下生气。 3. Reymet gave his shady uncle Venco some Senate Guard access codes in exchange for his help, but Venco plotted to use the codes to murder a Galactic Senator. 雷梅特把几段议会卫士密码泄露给他可疑的伯伯文科，以换取对方的帮助，但文科计划用这些密码谋杀一位银河共和国议员。', '副词: shadily 比较级: shadier 最高级: shadiest 名词: shadiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('carrot', '[\'kærət]', 'n.胡萝卜；<非>好处；报酬', '1. Have some more carrot. 再吃点胡萝卜。 2. The dish of boiled beef and carrot tastes good. 那道清炖牛肉胡萝卜的菜味道不错。 3. You should eat such vegetables as carrot, celery and spinach. 你应该吃胡萝卜、芹菜和菠菜这类的蔬菜。 4. The myth that eating carrot improved your eyesight was exploded years ago. 认为吃胡萝卜可以改善视力的海外奇谈，多年前已祛除殆尽。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('infer', '[ɪn\'fɜːr]', 'vt.推断；猜测；暗示 vi.作出推论', '1. We can infer the meaning of the word in the context. 我们可以从上下文中推断这个词的含义。 2. They infer a conclusion from the facts. 他们从事实中推断出结论。 3. I infer that my proposal has been accepted. 我推测我的建议已被接受。 4. Ragged clothing infers poverty. 衣衫褴褛意味着贫困。 5. We can infer from his expression that he is frustrated. 我们可以从他的表情中推断出他很沮丧。', '形容词: inferable 副词: inferably 名词: inferrer 过去式: inferred 过去分词: inferred 现在分词: inferring 第三人称单数: infers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('millionaire', '[ˌmɪljə\'ner]', 'n.百万富翁', '1. He spends as if he were a millionaire. 他用起钱来像个百万富翁似的。 2. Now a millionaire, he typifies the self-made man. 他成了百万富翁，可以说是白手起家的典型。 3. He is not poor, on the contrary, he is a millionaire. 他不穷，相反，他是个百万富翁。 4. The library\'s latest acquisitions were donated by a millionaire. 图书馆最近增添的书籍是一位百万富翁捐献的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seal', '[siːl]', 'n.封条；印章 n.海豹 v.密封；盖印；明确', '1. The seal on this bottle is broken. 这个瓶上的密封纸破开了。 2. This document carries the royal seal. 这份文件上盖有王室印章。 3. The first time I saw a seal was in an aquarium. 我第一次看见海豹是在水族馆里。 4. The envelope was firmly sealed. 这个信封封得很严实。', '形容词: sealable 过去式: sealed 过去分词: sealed 现在分词: sealing 第三人称单数: seals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lovely', '[\'lʌvli]', 'adj.可爱的；令人愉快的；好看的', '1. The girl\'s rosy cheeks made her look very lovely. 那女孩玫瑰色的脸颊使她显得非常可爱。 2. The squirrel is a lovely small animal. 松鼠是一种可爱的小动物。 3. Collecting buttons is a lovely way to pass time. 收集钮扣是一种令人愉快的消遣方法。 4. It\'s been a simply lovely afternoon. 今天下午真令人愉快。', '比较级: lovelier 最高级: loveliest 名词: loveliness 名词复数: lovelies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rod', '[rɑːd]', 'n.杆；棍棒；竿', '1. The concrete walls are reinforced with steel rods. 混凝土墙是用钢筋加固的。 2. He sank the metal rod in before the concrete set. 他在混凝土凝固之前把金属棒插了进去。 3. I knew I was in trouble when I was taken to the garage with a rod. 当我被人拿著棍棒赶到车库时,我知道我惹下麻烦了。 4. I bought a new fishing rod last Sunday. 上星期日我新买了一个鱼竿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('city', '[\'sɪti]', 'n.城市；都市；全体市民；特许市；特权市 City. n.（伦敦最古老的金融商务中心）伦敦商业区', '1. Beijing is a large city. 北京是一座大城市。 2. I live in the west of the city. 我住在该城市的西部。 3. The city is held by the enemy. 这座城市已被敌人占领。 4. He said he preferred country life to city life. 他说他喜欢乡下生活，而不喜欢都市生活。 5. She works in the City. 她在伦敦商业区工作。', '名词复数: cities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sick', '[sɪk]', 'adj.有病的；恶心的；腻烦的；晕的；令人毛骨悚然的 n.病人；呕吐物 vt.追逐；攻击；唆使', '1. He fell sick with malaria on a trip to Africa. 他在去非洲时患了疟疾。 2. He put a maid in to look after his sick wife. 他雇了1名女仆来照顾她的病妻。 3. You\'ll be sick if you eat any more of that candy. 如果你再吃那种糖果,就会感到恶心的。 4. I\'m sick of waiting around like this. 我讨厌透了像这样在一旁等著。 5. The sick need special care. 病人需要特别护理。 6. Sick\'em! 咬他们!', '比较级: sicker 最高级: sickest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('twenty', '[\'twenti]', 'num.二十', '1. We invited twenty people, but only a handful of them came. 我们邀请了20 个人，但只来了寥寥数人。 2. He lived in California until he was twenty. 他在加里弗尼亚一直住到20岁。 3. He was a famous artist in the twenties. 他在二十年代是一个著名的艺术家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('by', '[baɪ]', 'prep.靠近；通过；被；经由；不迟于 adv.经过；在旁边；靠近', '1. The house by the lake is a restaurant. 湖边的那座房子是家饭店。 2. He entered by the back door. 他从后门进入。 3. The project was viewed favorably by the committee. 那计划受到该委员会的好评。 4. He let himself down slowly by means of a rope. 他用一条绳子滑下来。 5. He hurried by and disappeared in the wood. 他匆匆走过去，消失在森林里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('third', '[θɜːrd]', 'num.第三；三分之一 adj.第三的；三分之一的', '1. The favourite came in third. 那个最有希望获胜的却跑了个第三名。 2. This tennis player ranked third in the world. 这位网球运动员排名世界第三。 3. The boss docked a third of my wages. 老板扣掉我三分之一工资。 4. His party has one third of the seats in Parliament. 他那个党在议会中占三分之一席位。 5. I have taken a third helping. 我已经吃了第三份食物了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cocaine', '[koʊ\'keɪn]', 'n.可卡因', '1. He was addicted to cocaine. 他吸可卡因上瘾。 2. Cocaine is a highly addictive drug. 可卡因是一种极为容易上瘾的毒品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cosy', '[\'koʊzi]', 'adj.舒适温暖的；亲切友好的；相互勾结的 n.保温套 v.讨好 =cozy（美）.', '1. He lives in a cosy little room. 他住在一个舒适的小屋里。 2. \"Oh dear,\" thought Brown, \"It\'s going to be one of those cosy chat sessions.\" “哦，天哪，”布朗想，“又得来一次亲切友好的谈话了。” 3. He has been accused of cosying up to the new US president. 他被指责讨好新任美国总统。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crowd', '[kraʊd]', 'n.人群；群众；大群；朋友 v.拥挤；挤满；涌入；贴近；逼迫', '1. We had to push our way through the crowd. 我们得从人群中挤过去。 2. From across the fields came cheers of the crowd. 从田野的那一边传来群众的欢呼声。 3. A large crowd was waiting at the bus stop. 一大群人在公共汽车站等候。 4. A crowd gathered at the scene of the fire. 许多人聚集在火灾现场。 5. They had managed to crowd into a train. 他们勉强挤上了一列火车。', '名词: crowder 过去式: crowded 过去分词: crowded 现在分词: crowding 第三人称单数: crowds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('religious', '[rɪ\'lɪdʒəs]', 'adj.宗教的；虔诚的；严谨的；信奉宗教的', '1. The religious affairs have been reestablished. 宗教事务已经恢复。 2. He was troubled by religious doubt. 他因对宗教的疑惧而十分烦恼。 3. Secular music refers to music which is not religious. 世俗音乐是指非宗教的音乐。 4. She is very religious and goes to church three times a week. 她非常虔诚，每周去教堂三次。', '副词: religiously 名词: religiousness 名词复数: religious');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bread', '[bred]', 'n.面包 vt.在 ... 上撒面包屑', '1. They had nothing to eat but stale bread. 除了陈面包外，他们没有别的东西可吃。 2. I had a frugal meal of bread and cheese last night. 我昨晚吃了只有面包和奶酪的便餐。 3. Bread the pork chops before frying them. 炸猪排前先在上面撒一点面包碎屑。', '过去式: breaded 过去分词: breaded 现在分词: breading 第三人称单数: breads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lung', '[lʌŋ]', 'n.肺；呼吸器官', '1. Smoking can cause lung cancer. 吸烟可致肺癌。 2. A bullet pierced his right lung. 一颗子弹洞穿他的右肺。 3. Smoking is responsible for many cases of lung cancer. 吸烟是许多人患肺癌的致病因素。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('provide', '[prə\'vaɪd]', 'v.供给；提供；准备；规定；抚养', '1. Sheep provide us with wool. 羊供给我们羊毛。 2. The hotel provides a reservation of tickets for its residents. 这家旅馆为旅客提供订票服务。 3. We have to provide for possible accidents. 我们要为可能发生的意外作些准备。 4. The law provides that these ancient buildings must be preserved. 法律规定，这些古老的建筑应该保存。', '过去式: provided 过去分词: provided 现在分词: providing 第三人称单数: provides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alive', '[ə\'laɪv]', 'adj.活着的；有活力的；注意到的；热闹的', '1. She clung to the hope that her son was still alive. 她始终抱着儿子还活着的希望。 2. Are your grandparents still alive? 你的祖父母还在世吗？ 3. Although he is eighty, he is still very much alive. 他虽有八十岁了，但仍然充满了活力。 4. He is fully alive to the possible dangers. 他充分注意到会有危险。', '名词: aliveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('driver', '[\'draɪvər]', 'n.驾驶员；司机；驱动器', '1. The driver slacked up on the gas pedal. 驾驶员松开油门减速。 2. A good driver keeps his eye on the road. 好的驾驶员会注意看路。 3. I\'m a hopeless driver, but the examiner let me through. 我开车的技术糟透了，但考官让我及格了。 4. The driver was not to blame for the accident. 这次事故怪不着司机。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('complicated', '[\'kɑːmplɪkeɪtɪd]', 'adj.复杂难懂的；结构复杂的 动词complicate的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The novel is too complicated for your age. 这小说就你的年龄来说太复杂了。 2. The tax laws are so complicated that only an expert can provide enlightenment. 税务法非常复杂，只有专家才能解释清楚。 3. Obtaining a refund from the company is a complicated procedure. 向公司索取退款手续很复杂。 4. An automobile is a complicated apparatus. 汽车是台复杂的机器.', '副词: complicatedly 名词: complicatedness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('boundary', '[\'baʊndri]', 'n.边界；分界线', '1. We crossed the state boundary at midnight. 我们在午夜穿过了州界。 2. They marked the boundaries of the football fields. 他们画出了足球场地的边界。 3. Scientists continue to push back the boundaries of knowledge. 科学家不断地把知识领域的边缘向外扩展。 4. The lane is the boundary of our land from theirs. 那条小路就是我们这片地与他们那片地的分界线。', '名词复数: boundaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remedy', '[\'remədi]', 'n.治疗法；药物；补救 vt.治疗；补救；矫正', '1. Warmth is the best remedy for colds. 热疗是治感冒的最好方法。 2. I can offer you a sure remedy. 我可以给你提供一个有效的疗法。 3. The remedy he purchased failed to work. 他买的药并不灵验。 4. The mistake is beyond remedy. 这个错误是无法补救的。 5. Aspirin may remedy a headache. 阿斯匹林可治头痛。', '名词复数: remedies 过去式: remedied 过去分词: remedied 现在分词: remedying 第三人称单数: remedies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('due', '[duː]', 'adj.应有的；到期的；预定的；应付的 n.应得物；会费', '1. When it comes to giving due respect to the old people, she feels a bit uneasy. 说到给老人应有的尊敬,她有些不自在。 2. The BBC must ensure that due impartiality is preserved in its news programmes. 英国广播公司必须确保新闻节目保持应有的公正。 3. If you\'re going to the library, would you mind returning this book for me? It\'s due today. 如果你要去图书馆的话,是否介意替我还一下这本书呢?它今天到期。 4. The English version of the novel is due for publication next year. 这部小说的英文译本预定明年出版发行。 5. He received a large reward, which was no more than his due. 他得到了一大笔奖金,这只是他应得的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('racket', '[\'rækɪt]', 'n.球拍 n.喧闹；敲诈；<俚>行业；职业 v.喧闹；花天酒地', '1. The ball just tipped the edge of his racket. 球仅仅碰到他球拍的边儿。 2. My hands blistered from holding the racket. 我的手因握球拍而起了水疱。 3. What a racket the children are making! 这些孩子太吵了！ 4. The students kicked up no end of a racket in the street. 这些学生在大街上大吵大闹。 5. The children always racket about in the courtyard. 孩子们总是在院子里吵吵闹闹。', '过去式: racketed 过去分词: racketed 现在分词: racketing 第三人称单数: rackets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('frank', '[fræŋk]', 'adj.坦白的；直率的；真诚的 vt.免费邮寄；使自由出入 n.免费邮寄；弗兰克（人名）', '1. A frank discussion can help to clear the air. 坦率的谈论有助于消除疑虑。 2. To be very frank, I think you have very little chance of getting the job. 坦白地说，我认为你获得这项工作的机会微乎其微。 3. He was frank, open and aboveboard. 他胸怀坦白，光明磊落。 4. They tend to be frank and open but alo self-centered and willful. 他们的性格坦诚、直率，但往往以自我为中心，并且任性妄为。 5. We are trying to frank him through customs. 我们正努力使他免检通过海关。', '比较级: franker 最高级: frankest 名词: frankness 过去式: franked 过去分词: franked 现在分词: franking 第三人称单数: franks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('which', '[wɪtʃ]', 'adj.哪一个；哪一些 pron.哪一个；哪些', '1. Which book have you read? 哪一本书你读过了？ 2. Here are the designs. Which ones do you prefer? 这就是那些图样。你喜欢哪一些? 3. It\'s hard to say which is better. 很难说哪一个好些。 4. Which are the best headache tablets? 哪些药片治头痛最好？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outlet', '[\'aʊtlet]', 'n.出路；出口；通风口；批发商店，经销店', '1. He needs an outlet for all that pent up anger. 他那积愤需要有机会倾吐. 2. Playing rock music is a good outlet for his energy. 弹奏摇滚乐是他发泄精力的好方法。 3. So long as you dare the inner ear, you can find the outlet truly. 只要你敢于迷路,你才能真正找到出路。 4. Do not sit or lean unnecessarily close to the airbag outlet. 如无必要,不要靠近气袋出口。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extra', '[\'ekstrə]', 'adj.额外的 n.额外之物；临时演员 adv.特别地', '1. There were so many people that the company put on extra buses. 人数太多，公司加开了公共汽车。 2. Guests at this hotel can use the gym at no extra cost. 这家饭店的客人们可以使用健身房,不再额外收费。 3. Her school fees are 440 a term; music and dancing are extras. 她的学费是每学期440英镑，音乐和舞蹈课另外收费。 4. We need hundreds of extras for the battle scenes. 我们拍战斗场面需要上百的临时演员。 5. We\'ll give you an extra special discount for buying this merchandise. 要是您购买这些商品,我们会给您非常特别的折扣。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quality', '[\'kwɑːləti]', 'n.品质；才能；特质 adj.高品质的；<英俚>棒极了', '1. He examined the quality of the furniture carefully. 他仔细检查家俱的品质。 2. Her most essential quality is kindness. 她最主要的品质是善良。 3. He shows quality of leadership. 他显示出领导才能。 4. What are the qualities that mark a great leader ? 伟大领袖的特质是什么? 5. Even the best quality rubber will perish with age. 就是最佳质量的橡胶也会因老化而腐烂。', '名词复数: qualities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('advertise', '[\'ædvərtaɪz]', 'v.登广告；宣传；告知', '1. We decided to advertise our new product. 我们决定为我们的新产品做广告。 2. We can advertise on the Internet. 我们可以在网上登广告。 3. I must advertise for a new secretary. 我得刊登广告聘请一位新秘书。 4. It was time to advertise our cause instead of our cars. 当时的当务之急是我们的事业可不是为我们的汽车进行广告宣传。', '名词: advertiser 过去式: advertised 过去分词: advertised 现在分词: advertising 第三人称单数: advertises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('melt', '[melt]', 'vi.融化；熔化；消散 vt.使融化；使熔化；使消散 n.熔化物；融化；熔解', '1. These chocolates really melt in your mouth. 这些巧克力真正是入口即化。 2. His heart melted when he saw the little girl crying. 看到这个小女孩哭起来，他的心软了。 3. If you warm ice it will melt into water. 如果你把冰加热，它会融化成水。 4. Metals will melt when heated to a certain temperature. 金属加热到一定的温度都会熔化。 5. The sun melted the snow. 太阳使雪融化。 6. If you warm ice it will melt into water. 如果你把冰加热，它会融化成水。', '形容词: meltable 副词: meltingly 名词: meltability 过去式: melted 过去分词: melted 现在分词: melting 第三人称单数: melts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shade', '[ʃeɪd]', 'n.阴影；遮蔽；遮光物；(色彩的)浓淡 vt.遮蔽；使阴暗；使渐变；略减（价格） vi.渐变', '1. This artist uses shade to good effect. 这位画家有效地利用阴影。 2. There are no trees or bushes to give shade. 没有树木或灌木丛可以遮荫。 3. Something,such as a window shade or a Venetian blind,that hinders vision or shuts out light. 遮光物如窗帘或软百叶窗等能遮挡视线或挡住阳光的物体。 4. The portrait shows fine effects of light and shade. 这幅肖像画的浓淡色调表现得很好。 5. He tried to shade his house with thick trees. 他想让这些大树把房子遮住。 6. The colors of the light shaded from blue into purple. 光线的颜色由蓝逐渐变紫。', '名词: shader 过去式: shaded 过去分词: shaded 现在分词: shading 第三人称单数: shades');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('involve', '[ɪn\'vɑːlv]', 'vt.包含；使忙于；牵涉；使卷入；使陷入', '1. A letter of credit will involve unnecessary extra charges. 信用证包含有不必要的额外开支。 2. The Genius is a lovable physicist who is deeply involved in defining the workings of the universe. 老天才是一位可爱的学者，他整天忙于解释天地间的各种现象。. 3. Don\'t involve other people in your trouble. 别把别人牵涉进你的麻烦中去。 4. I got involved in a quarrel about the price. 我被卷入了一场有关价格的争吵。', '名词: involvement 过去式: involved 过去分词: involved 现在分词: involving 第三人称单数: involves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dose', '[doʊs]', 'n.剂量；一剂；一服 vt.给 ... 服药', '1. Take one dose of this cough syrup three times a day. 每天服三次这种止咳糖浆，每次服一剂量。 2. The doctor prescribed an oral dose of medicine. 医生开了一剂口服药。 3. A dose of this medicine will put you right. 这药你只要服一剂，你的病就会好的。 4. Failing the exam was a hard dose to swallow. 考试不及格是一服难咽的苦药。 5. She dosed up the children with cough syrup. 她把止咳糖浆给孩子们吃了。', '名词: doser 过去式: dosed 过去分词: dosed 现在分词: dosing 第三人称单数: doses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crown', '[kraʊn]', 'n.王冠；王权；花冠；顶点；齿冠；克朗（丹麦、瑞典、捷克等国的货币单位） vt.加冕；使 ... 成王；居 ... 之顶；镶齿冠；使圆满；<口>打…的头部', '1. The crown was enchased with gold and silver. 这顶王冠上镶嵌着金和银。 2. She refused the crown. 她拒不接受王位。 3. I know she promised him a lilac crown. 我知道,她曾允诺他一顶紫丁香的花冠。 4. He cracked his crown on a microphone during a performance. 他在一次表演中在麦克风上把齿冠打破了。 5. They wanted to crown Caesar king . 他们想立凯撒为王。', '过去式: crowned 过去分词: crowned 现在分词: crowning 第三人称单数: crowns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('handicap', '[\'hændikæp]', 'n.障碍 vt.妨碍', '1. Blindness is a great handicap. 失明是极大的障碍。 2. Deafness can be a serious handicap. 耳聋算是严重的缺陷。 3. Poor eyesight is a handicap to a student. 视力不好对学生来说是一个障碍。 4. It takes a lot of grit to overcome a physical handicap. 要很大的毅力来克服生理上的障碍。 5. Ignorance can handicap the progress of a city. 无知会妨碍城市的进步。', '过去式: handicapped 过去分词: handicapped 现在分词: handicapping 第三人称单数: handicaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wrist', '[rɪst]', 'n.手腕；腕部', '1. He fell downstairs and broke his wrist. 他从楼梯跌下，摔伤了手腕。 2. She wears a ring round her wrist. 她的手腕上戴着一只镯子。 3. The nurse lapped a bandage round his wrist. 护士把他的腕部包上绷带。 4. I want a pair of wrist protectors. 我要一副护腕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forehead', '[\'fɔːrhed]', 'n.前额；前部', '1. She lightly touched his forehead. 她轻轻地摸了摸他的前额。 2. The horse has a splash of white on its forehead. 这匹马的前额上有一块白斑。 3. The forehead is small and narrow, assumes the triangle slightly, the top of the head front part is smooth, on behind skin scale fine grain shape. 头部窄小，略呈三角形，头顶前部平滑，头后部皮肤上秤细粒颗状。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reverse', '[rɪ\'vɜːrs]', 'v.逆转；倒退；互换；改变 adj.相反的；反面的；颠倒的 n.相反；背面；失败；倒档', '1. The government has failed to reverse the economic decline. 政府未能扭转经济滑坡的趋势。 2. He reversed the car into a tree. 他倒车撞到了树上。 3. Statistics showed a reverse trend to that recorded in other countries. 统计数字表明这种趋向与其他国家所示情况迥异。 4. Count down in reverse order 10, 9, 8... 倒数--10、 9、 8... 5. In hot weather, the reverse happens. 在热天,情况相反。', '副词: reversely 名词: reverser 过去式: reversed 过去分词: reversed 现在分词: reversing 第三人称单数: reverses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rock', '[rɑːk]', 'n.岩石；摇滚乐；困境 vt.使震惊；摇动；使动心 vi.来回摇动；跳摇摆舞', '1. The ship struck on a rock and sank. 船触礁沉没。 2. The deer is standing on the edge of the rock. 那只鹿正站在岩石的边缘。 3. The 1970s were best known for rock music. 20世纪70年代以摇滚乐而闻名。 4. Their marriage is on the rocks. 他们的婚姻濒于破裂 5. The news of the president\'s death rocked the nation. 总统过世的消息震惊了全国。 6. He rocked back and forth in his rocking chair. 他坐在摇椅里前后摇晃着。', '副词: rockingly 过去式: rocked 过去分词: rocked 现在分词: rocking 第三人称单数: rocks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pilgrim', '[\'pɪlɡrɪm]', 'n.朝圣者 Pilgrim. n.(1620年移居美洲的)英国清教徒', '1. We met many pilgrims on their way to Mecca. 我们遇到许多去麦加朝圣的人。 2. At length the pilgrim could shake the dust off his feet at Heidelberg. 那个朝圣者终于可以在海德堡停下来了。 3. I edged closer like a pilgrim approaching a shrine. 我像一位走近庙宇的朝圣者一样再往近走。 4. Their family goes back to the time of the Pilgrim Fathers. 他们家族的渊源可追溯到清教徒前辈移民时代。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('civilize', '[\'sɪvəlaɪz]', 'vt.使开化；使文明', '1. His wife has had a civilizing influence on him. 他妻子对改进他言谈举止有潜移默化的影响。 2. Many a rough man has been civilized by his wife. 许多粗野的男人在妻子的开导下变得文雅了。', '形容词: civilizable 名词: civilizer 过去式: civilized 过去分词: civilized 现在分词: civilizing 第三人称单数: civilizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('breach', '[briːtʃ]', 'n.破坏；违背；决裂；裂口；（浪的）冲击 v.违反；突破；在 ... 上打开缺口', '1. Union officials denounced the action as a breach of the agreement. 工会负责人谴责这一行动破坏了协议。 2. You are in breach of your contract. 你违反了你签的合同。 3. It caused a lifelong breach with his father. 这使得他们父子终身失和。 4. The huge waves made a breach in the sea wall. 大浪在堤上冲出一个缺口。 5. He never do the things breach the benefits of group. 他不做任何违背集体利益的事。', '过去式: breached 过去分词: breached 现在分词: breaching 第三人称单数: breaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('layoff', '[\'leɪˌɔːf]', 'n.临时解雇；操作停止；活动停止期间', '1. Stock prices broke when the firm suddenly announced layoffs. 当公司突然宣布裁员时，股票价格便大跌', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nowhere', '[\'noʊwer]', 'adv.任何地方都不 n.不知道的地方；无处', '1. Nowhere else will you find such a good book. 你在其他任何地方都找不到这么好的书。 2. The young girl would go nowhere without her chaperon. 这个年轻女孩去任何地方都有监护人跟着。 3. That kind of talk will get you nowhere. 说那种话对你没好处。 4. He\'s had nowhere to live since his eviction. 他自从被驱逐出住所以来，就一直无处栖身。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('active', '[\'æktɪv]', 'adj.活跃的；积极的；起作用的；灵活的', '1. Ms. Brown is active in the party. 布朗女士在晚会上很活跃。 2. He is an active member of the school\'s stamp club. 他是学校集邮俱乐部的一名活跃会员。 3. She was active as a left-winger in the party. 她是党内积极的左翼分子。 4. We should take active part in extracurricular activities. 我们应该积极参加课外活动。', '副词: actively 名词: activeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prosper', '[\'prɑːspər]', 'vi.繁盛；成功；兴旺', '1. We are bound to prosper beyond other countries. 我们肯定要比其他国家更兴旺繁荣。 2. The schemes of the wicked often prosper. 坏人的阴谋常常得逞。 3. She can\'t prosper on the course she\'s going now. 她现在所走的路是没有前途的。 4. With her at the wheel, the company began to prosper. 有了她当主管，公司开始兴旺起来。', '过去式: prospered 过去分词: prospered 现在分词: prospering 第三人称单数: prospers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chemist', '[\'kemɪst]', 'n.化学家；药剂师；药房', '1. Do you want anything from the chemist? 你想向化学家要些什么吗？ 2. The famous chemist won the Nobel Prize. 那个著名的化学家赢得了诺贝尔奖。 3. The chemist is preparing a medicine. 药剂师正在配药。 4. The woman went to the chemist\'s shop and showed the docter\'s note to the chemist. 这女人去了药师房，把医生写的那张纸条递给药剂师看。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('agree', '[ə\'ɡriː]', 'v.同意；赞成；承认；符合；一致', '1. We agreed to leave at once. 我们同意立即离开。 2. I, for my part, totally agree with you. 至於我,我完全同意你的看法。 3. I didn\'t agree from the very beginning. 我从一开始就不赞成。 4. We must agree to differ on this. 我们得承认在这一问题上有分歧。', '过去式: agreed 过去分词: agreed 现在分词: agreeing 第三人称单数: agrees');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('caress', '[kə\'res]', 'n.爱抚；拥抱 v.爱抚；抚摸；怜爱', '1. The lonely child is longing for the caress of his mother. 这个孤独的孩子渴望母亲的爱抚。 2. She feasted on the caress of the hot spring. 她尽情享受着温泉的抚爱。 3. He prescribed his fiancee\'s reception of his caress. 他要求他的未婚妻接受他的拥抱。 4. He caressed his wife lovingly. 他爱怜地抚摸着他的妻子。', '形容词: caressive 副词: caressingly 名词: caresser 过去式: caressed 过去分词: caressed 现在分词: caressing 第三人称单数: caresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soda', '[\'soʊdə]', 'n.汽水；苏打', '1. He gave me a bottle of orange soda. 他递给我一瓶桔子汽水。 2. They suck soda water through straws. 他们用吸管喝汽水。 3. You can\'t work on soda crackers and sardines. 你光吃苏打饼乾和沙丁鱼不行。 4. Please add some soda to the whisky. 请在威士忌中加些苏打水。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('underline', '[ˌʌndər\'laɪn]', 'v.在…下面划线；强调', '1. Please underline the important items. 请在重要事项的下面划线。 2. In writing you should underline titles of books. 写作时你该在书名下画线。 3. These different roles underline the importance of these cells. 这些不同的作用强调了这些细胞的重要性。', '过去式: underlined 过去分词: underlined 现在分词: underlining 第三人称单数: underlines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('military', '[\'mɪləteri]', 'adj.军事的 n.军队', '1. They are making further efforts to decrease military spending. 他们正在做进一步的努力来减少军费开支。 2. In some countries all the young men do a year\'s military service. 有些国家，所有年轻男子都要服一年兵役。 3. The military were called in to deal with the riot. 已将军队调来镇压暴乱。 4. The military has tightened its hold on the country. 军方加强了对这个国家的控制。', '副词: militarily 名词复数: military');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('circular', '[\'sɜːrkjələr]', 'adj.圆形的；循环的 n.传单；通报', '1. We can compute the circular area with radius. 我们能用半径计算出圆的面积。 2. The full moon has a circular form. 满月呈圆形。 3. Why the wedding ring is circular? 为什么结婚戒指是圆形的? 4. As long as no key is pressed, the scanning goes around in a circular manner. 只要没有按下键，扫描就循环地进行。 5. Have you seen that circular from the new furniture centre? 你见到那家本地新开的家俱总汇的广告了吗？', '副词: circularly 名词: circularity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recycle', '[ˌriː\'saɪkl]', 'vt.再利用；使再循环；再制 vi.循环 n.再循环', '1. We should try to recycle all our waste paper. 我们应该把所有废纸回收再利用。 2. One thing you can\'t recycle is wasted time. 唯一无法回收利用的是你浪费掉的时间。 3. We should recycle the used things. 我们应回收利用旧东西。 4. We must recycle the cardboard boxes. 我们必须循环使用纸盒子。 5. The ecological system can recycle by itself. 生态系统本身就可以循环。 6. Water recycle is a good way to save our resources. 水循环利用是一种很好的节约资源的方法。', '形容词: recyclable 名词: recycler 过去式: recycled 过去分词: recycled 现在分词: recycling 第三人称单数: recycles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peaceful', '[\'piːsfl]', 'adj.和平的；安宁的', '1. Hopes of a peaceful settlement are now fading. 和平解决的希望正在消失。 2. China is a peaceful country. 中国是一个爱好和平的国家。 3. The world today is far from peaceful. 今天的世界还很不安宁。 4. Law and order are necessary for a peaceful society. 法律和秩序对于社会安宁是必需的。', '副词: peacefully 名词: peacefulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('examine', '[ɪɡ\'zæmɪn]', 'vt.检查；调查；考试；仔细观察 vi.检查；调查', '1. The doctor examined her carefully. 医生仔细检查了她的身体。 2. Examine the account well before you pay it. 在付款以前仔细核对一下帐目。 3. He was unable to examine the issue with detachment. 他不能客观公正地调查这一问题。 4. The teacher will examine the students in English. 老师要考学生的英语了。 5. Examine the falsework of a house. 检查一座房屋的临时鹰架。', '形容词: examinable 名词: examiner 过去式: examined 过去分词: examined 现在分词: examining 第三人称单数: examines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('riddle', '[\'rɪdl]', 'n.谜；谜语 vt.解谜；出谜题；充满；打洞；筛选 vi.出谜题', '1. That painting is still a riddle to us. 那幅画对我们仍然是个谜。 2. He could not solve the riddle. 他猜不出这个谜。 3. He got the answer to the riddle as quick as a flash. 他一下子就猜中了谜底。 4. The riddle was at last unriddled. 这个谜语终于得到了解答。 5. She loved to riddle out the solution to problems. 她喜欢解答问题。', '名词: riddler 过去式: riddled 过去分词: riddled 现在分词: riddling 第三人称单数: riddles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('need', '[niːd]', 'v.需要；必需 n.需要；必要；缺乏 aux.需要，必须（无时态、人称变化，后与不带 to 的动词不定式连用，多用于疑问句和否定句）', '1. You look tired. You need a good rest. 你看来累了。你需要好好休息一下。 2. If I need you to come and help, I\'ll call you. 如果我需要你来帮忙,我会打电话的。 3. If the ground is too dry, then you need to water it. 如果地面太干燥,那么你就需要给它浇浇水。 4. You need some warm clothes for the winter. 冬天来了,你必需准备一些保暖衣物。 5. The doctor told me I was in need of a good rest. 医生对我说，我需要好好休息。', '过去式: needed 过去分词: needed 现在分词: needing 第三人称单数: needs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abundant', '[ə\'bʌndənt]', 'adj.丰富的；充裕的', '1. Indonesia is abundant in petroleum deposits. 印尼的石油蕴藏量丰富。 2. The agricultural commodities are abundant this year. 今年的农产品很丰富。 3. Birds concentrate in places where food is abundant. 鸟聚集在食物丰盛的地方。 4. There is abundant firewood in the forest. 森林里有充裕的薪柴可用。', '副词: abundantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('midst', '[mɪdst]', 'n.中间；当中 prep.在 ... 当中(=amidst)', '1. He was but recently in our midst. 他只是最近才到我们中间。 2. In his escape, he walked six days in the midst of howling wilderness. 在逃亡期间，他在人迹罕至的旷野中走了6天。 3. We must weed out the traitors in our midst! 我们必须清除我们中间的叛徒! 4. The girls had got on well together until the apple of discord in the person of a handsome young man arrived in their midst. 姑娘们一直相处很好，后来一个英俊的小伙子来到她们中间，引起了她们之间的不和。 5. So Paul went out from their midst. 于是保罗从他们当中出去了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('portrait', '[\'pɔːrtrət]', 'n.肖像；画像；描写', '1. He is a portrait painter. 他是一个肖像画家。 2. The portrait of her mother was her most prized possession. 她母亲的这张肖像是她最珍爱的物品。 3. I unearthed the portrait from the attic. 我从阁楼上搜出这幅画像。 4. In the portrait he is shown lying on a sofa. 在这张画像中画着他躺在沙发上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('punch', '[pʌntʃ]', 'vt.按(键)；以拳重击；开洞；剪票 n.殴打 n.打洞器；钻孔机 n.感染力 n.（酒、水、糖等制成的)鸡尾酒', '1. If you punch in the wrong code, the alarm sounds. 如果你按错了代码,警示器就会响起来。 2. He punched the policeman on the nose and was arrested. 他猛击那个警察的鼻子，结果被逮捕了。 3. The conductor punched his bus ticket. 售票员用剪票夹在他的汽车票上打孔。 4. The punch stunned me for a moment. 那一拳把我打得昏了一阵。 5. Many British movies lack emotional punch. 很多英国电影缺乏感染力。 6. Sometimes even a bowl of fruit punch could make people drunk. 有时候即使一碗水果鸡尾酒,人们也可能会喝醉。', '形容词: punchless 过去式: punched 过去分词: punched 现在分词: punching 第三人称单数: punches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compile', '[kəm\'paɪl]', 'vt.编译；编制；编纂', '1. Your first program is ready to compile and run. 你的第一个程序可以编译和运行了。 2. We are trying to compile a list of suitable people for the job. 我们在努力编制一份适合做这项工作的人员的名单。 3. How do we compile a balance of payments statements? 我们如何编制收支平衡表? 4. It takes many years of hard work to compile a good dictionary. 编纂一部好词典要花多年心血。', '过去式: compiled 过去分词: compiled 现在分词: compiling 第三人称单数: compiles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('toilet', '[\'tɔɪlət]', 'n.厕所；盥洗室；卫生间', '1. Where is the ladies\' toilet? 女厕所在那里？ 2. Every flat has its own bathroom and toilet. 每套公寓都带有洗澡间和盥洗室。 3. I must buy some toilet requisites. 我必须买些卫生间必需品。 4. The sewer in the toilet was blocked. 卫生间的下水道堵住了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('every', '[\'evri]', 'adj.每个；一切的；所有可能的；每隔；最大的', '1. Every citizen should be obedient to the law. 每个公民都应当是遵守法律的。 2. He received the fixed dole every month. 他每个月都能领到固定的救济金。 3. I have had to work for every single penny I earned. 我挣的每一便士都是辛苦工作得来的。 4. He has read every book on the shelves. 书架上所有的书他都读过了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('correct', '[kə\'rekt]', 'adj.正确的；得体的 v.改正；纠正', '1. Your answer to the question is correct. 你对这个问题的回答是正确的。 2. So far no correct conclusion has arrived at. 到目前为止,还没有得出任何正确的结论。 3. Such casual dress would not be correct for a formal occasion. 这样的便服不宜在正式的场合穿。 4. Correct the errors in the following sentences, if any. 如果下列句子中有错,请改正。', '形容词: correctable 副词: correctly 名词: correctness 过去式: corrected 过去分词: corrected 现在分词: correcting 第三人称单数: corrects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('zip', '[zɪp]', 'n.拉链 n.活力；飞射声 v.拉拉链 v.飕飕飞过；注入活力', '1. She caught her hair in the zip of the dress. 她的头发被裙子的拉链钩住了。 2. The zip sticked because it was caught by a thread. 拉链被线卡住了, 拉不动。 3. We need to put some zip into this presentation. 我们需要为这次演出注人一些活力。 4. We had heard the zip of a bullet. 我们听到了子弹的咻的一声。 5. Please help me to zip my dress on. 请帮我把衣服的拉链拉上。 6. Rifle fire zipped over them. 步枪子弹在他们头顶上飕飕飞驰。', '过去式: zipped 过去分词: zipped 现在分词: zipping 第三人称单数: zips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cyberspace', '[\'saɪbərspeɪs]', 'n.网络空间', '1. In this cyberspace, I hope I can find a listener. 在这个网络空间，我希望可以找到一个倾听者。 2. They have declared war on Cyberspace. 他们已经在网络空间中宣战了！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('September', '[sep\'tembər]', 'n.九月', '1. The temperature drops in September. 气温在九月间下降。 2. We\'ve had to put our wedding off until September. 我们得把婚礼延期到九月举行。 3. The industrial exposition will be held on September. 工业博览会将于九月召开。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stationary', '[\'steɪʃəneri]', 'adj.静止的，不动的；稳定的 n.驻军', '1. He crashed into a stationary bus. 他撞了一辆停着不动的公共汽车。 2. A stationary object is easy to be aimed at. 一个静止不动的物体是容易瞄准的。 3. An astronaut will attempt to leave the stationary spaceship and then return to it. 一名宇航员试着离开静止不动的宇宙飞船，然后再返回。', '名词: stationariness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mislead', '[ˌmɪs\'liːd]', 'vt.误导；使产生错误印象；欺骗；使误入歧途', '1. What you said may mislead your students. 你所说的或许会误导学生。 2. A description about a product should not mislead the customers. 产品的说明书不能误导顾客。 3. By assaulting it, I intend to mislead the enemy. 我打算用假象欺骗敌人。 4. Dolgorukov was still insisting on his opinion that the French were retreating, and had only lighted fires to mislead them. 多尔戈鲁科夫一直坚持自己的意见，硬说法军撤退了，他们四处点火，只是妄想欺骗我们罢了。', '名词: misleader 过去式: misled 过去分词: misled 现在分词: misleading 第三人称单数: misleads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('all', '[ɔːl]', 'adj.所有的；全部的 adv.完全；都；非常 pron.一切；全部 n.全部', '1. All wood tends to shrink. 所有木头都会缩一些. 2. All my plants have died. 我的花草全死光了。 3. He spent all his time reading. 他把全部时间都花在阅读上。 4. His temperature seems to be all right. 他的体温好像完全正常。 5. We are grateful to you for all you have done. 我们对你所做的一切表示感谢。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grass', '[ɡræs]', 'n.草；草地 vt.喂(草)；(以草)覆盖；告发', '1. The grass was wet with dew. 草被露水打湿了。 2. Father was cutting the grass, and meanwhile mother was planting roses. 父亲在剪草,母亲在种玫瑰。 3. We play football on the grass. 我们在草地上踢足球。 4. She sat down on a tuft of grass. 她坐在一小块草地上。 5. They put out their horse to grass every day. 他们每天把马放出去吃草。', '过去式: grassed 过去分词: grassed 现在分词: grassing 第三人称单数: grasses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aesthetic', '[es\'θetɪk]', 'adj.美学的；审美的；有美感的 n.(复数)审美观', '1. Later he also gained in aesthetic knowledge. 后来他的美学知识也增加了。 2. From an aesthetic point of view it\'s a thetic view. 从美学观点来说, 这是个武断的看法。 3. The professor advanced a new aesthetic theory. 那位教授提出了新的美学理论。 4. His aesthetic ideas were his own. 他有他自己的审美观念。 5. Natural aesthetic is the core of Chinese aesthetics. 自然审美是中国古代美学的核心。', '副词: aesthetically 异体字: esthetic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('noticeable', '[\'noʊtɪsəbl]', 'adj.显而易见的；显著的；值得注意的', '1. The scar on her forehead is hardly noticeable. 她额头上的伤疤不太明显。 2. There\'s been a noticeable improvement in her handwriting. 她的书法有了明显的进步。 3. His good humour was particularly noticeable. 他的幽默感是显而易见的。 4. The specialists did not uncover any noticeable deviations from the norm. 专科医师并未发现任何值得注意的异状。', '副词: noticeably 名词: noticeability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disturbance', '[dɪ\'stɜːrbəns]', 'n.扰乱；骚动', '1. He was imprisoned for creating public disturbance. 他因扰乱公共治安而坐牢。 2. The drunken man was run in for creating a public disturbance. 那个醉汉因扰乱公共秩序而被拘留。 3. They were charged by the police with causing a disturbance. 他们被警方控告引起骚动。 4. The noise of cars passing along the road is a continual disturbance to our quiet at home. 马路上来往的车辆声音不断地破坏我们家的安宁。', '动词: disturb 形容词: disturbing 副词: disturbingly 名词复数: disturbances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alternate', '[\'ɔːltərnət]', 'v.交替；轮流 adj.间隔的；轮流的；交替的 n.代替者；供替代的选择', '1. Sunny weather alternated with rain. 天气晴雨相间。 2. One should alternate work and relaxation. 工作和休息应交替进行。 3. We alternate in cleaning the room. 我们轮流打扫房间。 4. Meetings are held on alternate Thursdays. 每隔一个星期的星期四举行一次会议。 5. My alternate knows my role really well, she\'s almost better than me. 我的接替者对我的工作非常了解，她甚至比我都好。', '副词: alternately 名词: alternateness 过去式: alternated 过去分词: alternated 现在分词: alternating 第三人称单数: alternates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mental', '[\'mentl]', 'adj.思想的；心理的；精神的；脑力的 n.精神病患者', '1. It\'s clear that mental activity does not stop when we\'re asleep. 很显然,我们熟睡的时候,思想活动仍然不会停下来。 2. We should pay more attention to our mental health. 我们应该更注重心理健康。 3. I think such mental disorders are hereditary. 我认为这种精神失调是遗传的。 4. Social life is developed by physical labor and mental labor. 社会生活由于体力劳动和脑力劳动的结合才得以发展。 5. The hospital cares for some fifty mental patients. 这家医院照料五十名左右精神病患者。', '副词: mentally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('import', '[\'ɪmpɔːrt]', 'n.进口；意义；进口商品 v.进口；输入', '1. The government has imposed strict controls over the import of luxury goods. 政府对奢侈品的进口采取了严格的管制。 2. You should grasp the import of your mother\'s remarks. 你应该领会到你妈妈说话的含义。 3. The miscellaneous expenses of import are so much! 进口货物的杂费太多了！ 4. It is profitable to import food. 进口食品可赚钱。', '形容词: importable 名词: importability 过去式: imported 过去分词: imported 现在分词: importing 第三人称单数: imports');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compress', '[\'kɑːmpres]', 'vt.压缩；压榨 n.[医]敷布', '1. Compress this clay into a small ball. 把这块粘土压缩成一个小球。 2. Click the picture that you want to compress. 单击要压缩的图片。', '过去式: compressed 过去分词: compressed 现在分词: compressing 第三人称单数: compresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stress', '[stres]', 'n.压力；强调；重音 vt.强调；重读', '1. Stress can be extremely damaging to your health. 压力对你的健康会是非常有害的。 2. The stress on setting an example is particularly necessary at present. 现在，强调以身作则这个问题很必要。 3. Which syllable does the stress of this word fall on? 这个单词的重音是在哪个音节上? 4. Here I will stress the importance of mathematics to the whole of science. 这里我要强调数学对整个科学的重要性。', '过去式: stressed 过去分词: stressed 现在分词: stressing 第三人称单数: stresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('insurance', '[ɪn\'ʃʊrəns]', 'n.保险；保险费；安全保障', '1. I am an insurance broker. 我是一名保险经纪人。 2. He works in an insurance company. 他在一家保险公司上班。 3. I have paid my car insurance. 我已经交了汽车保险费。 4. His insurance is $ 300 a year. 他的保险费是每年三百美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slight', '[slaɪt]', 'adj.轻微的；纤弱的；微小的 vt.轻视；忽略 n.轻蔑；怠慢', '1. He has a slight wheeze in his chest. 他呼吸时胸部发出轻微的响声。 2. Our army suffered a slight reverse. 我们的部队受到轻微的挫败。 3. The salve will heal slight burns. 这药膏能治疗轻微烧伤。 4. Her slight frame was shaken by bouts of coughing. 她纤弱的身躯因阵阵咳嗽而发颤。 5. We shouldn\'t slight anybody even if he\'s a nobody. 我们不应该轻视任何人，即使他是一个小人物。 6. I was hurt by the obvious slight. 这种明显的怠慢伤害了我的感情。', '比较级: slighter 最高级: slightest 名词: slightness 过去式: slighted 过去分词: slighted 现在分词: slighting 第三人称单数: slights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dense', '[dens]', 'adj.密集的；稠密的；浓密的', '1. My hometown is a large city with a dense population. :我的家乡是个人口密集的大城市。 2. Books with dense print can be difficult to read. 印得密密麻麻的书阅读起来很困难。 3. A dense mass of black hair framed his face. 浓密的黑发衬托着他的面庞。 4. They hewed their way through the dense jungle. 他们在浓密的丛林里开辟出一条路来。', '副词: densely 比较级: denser 最高级: densest 名词: denseness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('article', '[\'ɑːrtɪkl]', 'n.文章；物品；条款；[语]冠词 vt.订契约', '1. She asked him to contribute a biweekly article on European affairs. 她让他每两周写一篇有关欧洲情况的文章。 2. If you don\'t return the article to the shop within a week, you forfeit your chance of getting your money back. 如果你不把物品归还商店，你就丧失了取回钱的机会。 3. Article 180 states that one third of the members must be women. 第180条规定,三分之一的成员必须为女性。 4. Today we\'ll discuss the use of the article. 今天我们讨论冠词的用法。 5. I am articled to a firm of lawyers. 我受雇在一家律师公司做见习生。', '过去式: articled 过去分词: articled 现在分词: articling 第三人称单数: articles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('applause', '[ə\'plɔːz]', 'n.鼓掌；喝彩；赞许', '1. His speech won the applause of the audience. 他的讲话赢得了听众的掌声。 2. Let\'s have a good round of applause for the next performer. 咱们为下一个表演者热烈鼓掌吧。 3. His speech was frequently interrupted by stormy applause. 他的演说不时被暴风雨般的掌声打断。 4. He waited until the applause had subsided. 他一直等到掌声平息后才继续下去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('marvelous', '[\'mɑːvələs]', 'adj.令人惊异的；非凡的 =<英>marvellous', '1. He had had the most marvelous experience. 他有过极奇特的经历。 2. These dogs have a marvelous sense of smell. 这些狗有非常敏锐的嗅觉。 3. You have a marvelous gift for science. 你有科学方面的非凡天赋。 4. Their performance was marvelous. 他们的演出太精彩了。', '副词: marvelously 名词: marvelousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('solution', '[sə\'luːʃn]', 'n.解决办法；解答；溶液；溶解；设计', '1. He reasoned out a solution to the problem. 他经过推断,找出了解决问题的办法。 2. We haven\'t found the solution yet, but I\'m sure we\'re on the right track. 我们还没有找到解决办法，但我肯定我们的思路是对的。 3. The solution of the problem has just come to me. 我刚想起如何解答这个问题。 4. What color is copper sulphate solution? 硫酸铜溶液是什么颜色？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('typist', '[\'taɪpɪst]', 'n.打字员', '1. She worked as a typist in a law firm. 她在一家律师事务所当打字员。 2. Our typist is away on holiday this week. 我们这儿的打字员这星期因休假没上班。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('induce', '[ɪn\'duːs]', 'vt.引起；促使；劝服；引诱', '1. The medicine will induce sleep. 这种药会引起睡意。 2. They hoped their work would induce social changes. 他们希望自己的工作可以引起社会上的某些变化。 3. I can\'t think what induced her to marry him. 我想不出到底是什么原因促使她嫁给他。 4. Alcohol can induce a loosening of the tongue. 酒精可使人信口开河。', '形容词: inducible 过去式: induced 过去分词: induced 现在分词: inducing 第三人称单数: induces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('although', '[ɔːl\'ðoʊ]', 'conj.虽然；尽管；然而；可是', '1. Although my uncle is old, he looks very strong and healthy. 我的叔叔虽然老了，但他看上去还是很健壮。 2. Although they can swim, the polar bears are terrestrial animals. 北极熊虽然会游泳，但也是陆栖动物。 3. Although she was poor, she was living in genteel poverty. 尽管她贫穷，但她总想装出上流社会阶层的样子。 4. No, this is not what we mean by framing, although the principle is the same. 不,这不是我们所讲的框架的含义,尽管法则是一样的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stumble', '[\'stʌmbl]', 'v.绊倒；蹒跚；犯错误；无意中发现 n.绊倒；错误', '1. I stumbled over a tree root. 我在一个树根上绊了一跤。 2. Any man may stumble into crime when among criminals. 同犯罪分子混在一起,任何人都可能失足犯罪。 3. Any man may stumble into crime when among criminals. 同犯罪分子混在一起,任何人都可能失足犯罪。 4. You never knew when you might stumble across some new talent. 谁也说不准什么时候会碰上一位新的天才。 5. The horse recovered itself after stumble. 马绊倒后又站起来了。', '副词: stumblingly 名词: stumbler 过去式: stumbled 过去分词: stumbled 现在分词: stumbling 第三人称单数: stumbles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exhibit', '[ɪɡ\'zɪbɪt]', 'v.展览；陈列；展示；表现 n.展品；展览', '1. Many unearthed cultural relics were exhibited at the museum. 博物馆展出了许多出土文物。 2. He was given a whole room to exhibit his paintings. 整个房间用来展览他的画作。 3. She exhibited great powers of endurance during the climb. 她在攀登过程中表现出极大的耐力。 4. They deprecated the new exhibit. 他们很不赞成新展品。', '形容词: exhibitory 名词: exhibitor 过去式: exhibited 过去分词: exhibited 现在分词: exhibiting 第三人称单数: exhibits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guilt', '[ɡɪlt]', 'n.罪行；内疚', '1. We now have the absolute proof of his guilt. 我们现在有他犯罪的确凿证据。 2. The king was infamous for his guilt of many infamies. 那个国王因罪恶多端而臭名昭著。 3. His friend corroborated his guilt. 他的朋友证实了他的犯罪。 4. The law presumes innocence until guilt is proved. 在罪状未证实前，法律假定被告无罪。', '形容词: guilty 副词: guiltily');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('emphasis', '[\'emfəsɪs]', 'n.强调；重点；[语]加强语气', '1. They put emphasis on making to quota this quarter. 他们强调要达到这一季的配额。 2. Our English course places great emphasis on conversational skills. 我们的英语课程非常重视会话技能。 3. In recent years, the emphasis has moved away from punishing drug addicts towards helping them. 最近几年,重点从惩罚吸毒者转移到救助他们。 4. You put too much emphasis on the last syllable. 你把最后一个音节读得太重。', '名词复数: emphases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cradle', '[\'kreɪdl]', 'n.摇篮；发祥地；支架 v.怀抱', '1. The child slept soundly in her cradle. 那孩子在摇篮里睡得很熟。 2. Life is a battle from cradle to grave . 人生是从摇篮到坟墓的一场搏斗。 3. The sea is thought to have been the cradle of life. 人们认为海洋是生命的发源地。 4. Greece was the cradle of Western civilization. 希腊是西方文明的发祥地。', '名词: cradler 过去式: cradled 过去分词: cradled 现在分词: cradling 第三人称单数: cradles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('typhoon', '[taɪ\'fuːn]', 'n.台风', '1. The typhoon is gathering strength. 台风的风力正逐渐增强。 2. The typhoon hit the coastal area. 台风侵袭沿海地区。 3. The navy rescued forty people in the typhoon. 海军在台风天时救了四十个人。 4. The typhoon pulled up many trees by the roots. 台风把许多树连根拔了起来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('municipal', '[mjuː\'nɪsɪpl]', 'adj.市政的；市的 n.政府证券', '1. An angry mob gathered outside the municipal building. 一群愤怒的暴民聚集在市政大楼的外面。 2. The municipal authorities put forth a new set of traffic regulations some time ago. 前不久市政当局公布了一套新的交通法规。 3. She works in a municipal library. 她在一所市立的图书馆工作。 4. Mr. Charles was elected chairman of the municipal education committee. 查尔斯先生当选为市教育委员会的主任。', '副词: municipally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inward', '[\'ɪnwərd]', 'adj.内部的；内心的；向内的；亲密的 adv.向内 n.内部；内在', '1. The explorers discovered an inward passage. 探险队员发现了一条内部通道。 2. I understand your inward thoughts. 我了解你内心的思想。 3. His shaking hands showed his inward fear. 他颤抖的双手显示出他内心的恐惧。 4. The inward curve made the circle a whole. 这段向内的弧使这个圆完整了。 5. The door opened inward into the room. 门是朝房间里面开的。 6. As you surrender, direct your attention inward to check if there is any trace of resistance left inside you. 当你托付的时候，把注意力朝着内部引入，检查一下是否内部有任何抵抗残留迹象。', '副词: inwards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discrepancy', '[dɪs\'krepənsi]', 'n.差异；不一致；分歧', '1. We\'d like to discuss the details of the contract, especially discrepancy and claim. 我们想讨论合同的各项细目,特别是差异和索赔。 2. The price tag says$100 and you charged me for$120; how do you explain the discrepancy? 货物标签上写的是一百美元,你向我索价一百二十美元,这个差异该怎么解释？ 3. There was a discrepancy in the two reports. 在两个报告中有不一致之处。 4. Shakespeare did not acquiesce in discrepancy. 莎士比亚对于分歧并不是采取默认的态度。', '名词复数: discrepancies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('puppet', '[\'pʌpɪt]', 'n.木偶；傀儡', '1. He jerked the string and the puppet jumped. 他猛地一拉绳子，木偶就跳了起来。 2. How do you work these puppets? 你怎么操作这些木偶呢？ 3. Most kids love puppet shows. 大部分的孩子喜欢木偶节目。 4. Are we the puppets of fate? 我们是听任命运摆布的傀儡吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('constant', '[\'kɑːnstənt]', 'adj.不变的；经常的 n.常数；恒量', '1. In our world nothing seems constant. 在我们这个世界上似乎没有东西是永恒不变的。 2. The birth rate in this city is almost constant. 这城市的出生率几乎是不变的。 3. The machinery requires constant maintenance. 这些机器需要经常保养维修。 4. The constant friction between the young couple finally caused divorce. 小夫妻俩之间经常的冲突终于导致了离婚。 5. The speed of light is an important constant. 光速是一个重要的常数。', '副词: constantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('magnet', '[\'mæɡnət]', 'n.磁铁；有吸引力的人（物）', '1. He picked all the pins up with a magnet. 他用磁铁捡起了所有的大头针。 2. He was deeply attracted by the delicate cast of her features. 他的前途取决于这一机会。 3. Forbidden City is a great magnet for foreign tourists. 紫禁城对外国旅游者来说是个有巨大吸引力的地方。 4. The beautiful actress was the magnet that drew great audiences. 那个漂亮的女演员对很多观众都很有吸引力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bed', '[bed]', 'n.床；基座；底层；河床；花坛；苗圃；地层 v.安置；发生性关系', '1. Life isn\'t a bed of roses. 人生并非事事称心如意。 2. Can you give me a bed for the night? 你能给我安置一个床铺过夜吗？ 3. The machine rests on a bed of concrete. 机器安装在混凝土基座上。 4. The water is infiltrating the gravel bed. 水正渗透进碎石底层。 5. Can Mary bed down with her sister? 玛丽可不可以跟她姐妹同睡一床？', '过去式: bedded 过去分词: bedded 现在分词: bedding 第三人称单数: beds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('embody', '[ɪm\'bɑːdi]', 'vt.使具体化；包含；代表，体现；使(精神)肉体化', '1. The country\'s constitution embodies the ideals of freedom and equality. 这个国家的宪法体现了自由和平等的理想。 2. He embodies a new idea in his paintings. 他在画中体现思想。 3. The latest computer model embodies many new features. 最新型的计算机具备许多新功能。 4. The new car embodies many improvements. 这辆新车包含了许多改进的项目。', '过去式: embodied 过去分词: embodied 现在分词: embodying 第三人称单数: embodies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('according', '[ə\'kɔːdɪŋ]', 'adv.根据；按照 adj.相符的，一致的，相应的；和谐的，调和的', '1. According to expert opinions, they gave up the experiment immediately. 根据专家们的意见，他们马上放弃了这项试验。 2. According to facts in my possession he can not possibly be guilty. 根据我所掌握的事实，他是不可能有罪的。 3. According to our records, the books you have borrowed should now be returned to the library. 根据我们的记录，你借的书现在应该还给图书馆了。 4. According to these figures, our company is doing well. 从这些数字来看，我们的公司经营得不错。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hundred', '[\'hʌndrəd]', 'num.百 n.一百元 （复）hundreds: 成百上千；许多.', '1. Put two noughts after a seven to make seven hundred. 在7后面加两个零成为700。 2. The allied warplanes bombed the country by the hundred. 盟军数以百计的飞机轰炸了那个国家。 3. There are more than five hundred people on the playground. 运动场上有五百多人。 4. Five hundred jobs were axed as a result of government spending cuts. 由于政府缩减经费的缘故，有五百人被突然解雇了。 5. Can you change a hundred for five twenties? 你能把一百块找成五张二十块吗？', '名词复数: hundred');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('groan', '[ɡroʊn]', 'v.呻吟；抱怨；发嘎吱声；受重压 n.呻吟；呻吟声', '1. The girl groaned in pain. 那女孩在痛苦中呻吟。 2. He was heard to groan. 有人听见他在呻吟。 3. Don\'t moan and groan because of a little setback. 不要受了一点挫折就唉声叹气。 4. The roof creaked and groaned under the weight of the snow. 屋顶被积雪压得发出吱吱嘎嘎的声响。 5. The wounded man uttered a groan. 那个受伤的人发出呻吟。', '副词: groaningly 名词: groaner 过去式: groaned 过去分词: groaned 现在分词: groaning 第三人称单数: groans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overcoat', '[\'oʊvərkoʊt]', 'n.外套；大衣', '1. He turned his overcoat collar up. 他把外套的衣领翻了起来。 2. Although I am wearing an overcoat, I am still cold. 虽然我穿了件外套，但还是觉得冷。 3. That overcoat should see me through the winter. 有那件大衣我应该能过冬了。 4. She didn\'t put on an overcoat though it was very cold outside. 外头虽冷，她却没披件外套。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('duplicate', '[\'duːplɪkət]', 'n.副本 adj.完全一样的；复制的 v.复制；重复', '1. This is a duplicate. 这是个副本。 2. It\'s a duplicate set of keys 这是和另一套完全相同的钥匙. 3. Here is a duplicate copy. 这是份复制的文本。 4. Please duplicate the document for me! 请帮我复写下这份公文。', '形容词: duplicable 副词: duplicately 过去式: duplicated 过去分词: duplicated 现在分词: duplicating 第三人称单数: duplicates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('phenomenon', '[fə\'nɑːmɪnən]', 'n.现象；奇人；奇事', '1. Their so-called prosperity is only a temporary phenomenon. 但他们所谓的繁荣只是一个暂时的现象。 2. International terrorism is not just a recent phenomenon. 国际恐怖主义并不是近年才有的现象。 3. Magnetism is a natural phenomenon. 磁力是一种自然现象。 4. A child who could read at the age of one would indeed be a phenomenon. 一个一岁的孩子能阅读，会被认为是个神童。', '名词复数: phenomena');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('temperament', '[\'temprəmənt]', 'n.气质；性情', '1. He really has a leader temperament. 他真的有些领袖气质。 2. He is a man with an artistic temperament. 他是个有艺术家气质的男子。 3. I\'ve got a mild temperament. 我的性情很温和。 4. The two brothers have entirely different temperaments. 他们兄弟俩的性情完全不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('familiar', '[fə\'mɪliər]', 'adj.熟悉的；不拘礼节的；熟知的 n.熟人；精灵', '1. I am not really familiar with the local laws. 实际上我对当地的法律并不熟。 2. This nursery rhyme is very familiar to me. 我对这首摇篮曲很熟悉。 3. The children are too familiar with their teacher. 这帮小学生对老师过于随便。 4. He looks so familiar but I can\'t remember his name. 他看上去非常面熟，但我想不起他的名字来了。 5. She looked around for a familiar face. 她环顾四周想寻找一个熟人。', '副词: familiarly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('row', '[roʊ]', 'n.排；划船；路；吵闹 v.划船；将...排成排；吵架', '1. Students stand hand in hand in a row. 学生们手牵手站成一排。 2. He glanced towards the row of girls. 他拿眼把那一排女孩子一溜。 3. They asked me to go for a row with them. 他们邀请我和他们一道去划船。 4. Manor Row 庄园路 5. Can you row me up/across the river? 你能划船将我送到河的上游/对岸吗?', '名词: rower 过去式: rowed 过去分词: rowed 现在分词: rowing 第三人称单数: rows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('identical', '[aɪ\'dentɪkl]', 'adj.同一的；相同的', '1. This is the identical hotel we stayed at last year. 这就是我们去年住过的旅馆。 2. Your appearance is identical to hers. 你的相貌和她的一模一样。 3. They\'re wearing identical clothes. 他们穿着完全相同的衣服。', '副词: identically 名词: identicalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slip', '[slɪp]', 'v.滑倒；滑脱；疏忽；溜走 n.疏忽；滑倒；溜走；失误', '1. She slipped on the ice. 她在冰上滑倒了。 2. I was unlucky to slip on a banana skin and fall over. 我真倒霉，踩在香蕉皮上滑倒了。 3. The gear slipped. 齿轮滑脱了 4. The wheel slipped from my frozen hand, and the car went right across the road. 方向盘从我冻僵的手里滑脱, 汽车便横着穿过了马路。 5. Leaving his name off the list was a bad slip up. 名单上没有他的名字是个严重的疏忽。', '过去式: slipped 过去分词: slipped 现在分词: slipping 第三人称单数: slips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('try', '[traɪ]', 'v.试验；尝试；设法；努力；审判；考验 n.尝试；试验；（橄榄球）持球触地得分', '1. This idea seems good but you need to try it out. 这个想法似乎不错,但是需要试验一下。 2. I think I\'ll try my luck at roulette. 我想玩玩轮盘赌碰碰运气。 3. He is trying his best to understand his meaning. 他正在尽力弄明白他的意思。 4. Don\'t try to smooth over your faults. 不要设法掩饰你的过错。 5. After a few tries they decided to give up. 试了几次后，他们决定放弃。', '名词复数: tries 过去式: tried 过去分词: tried 现在分词: trying 第三人称单数: tries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('match', '[mætʃ]', 'n.对手；火柴；比赛；配偶；般配的人 v.相配；和...相配；相一致；较量', '1. He was very good at tennis, but he met his match when he played McEnroe. 他的网球打得很好，但当他与麦肯罗对打时，他遇到对手了。 2. I am no match for her when it comes to language. 在语言能力方面我根本不是她的对手。 3. The smoker tossed away the lighted match and so caused a fire. 那个抽烟的人随手扔掉火柴棒，引起了一场火灾。 4. A high standard of play marked the match between the two teams. 这两个队的比赛表现了很高的技术水平。 5. Will you match me this cloth? 你可以帮我搭配一下这块布料吗?', '名词: matcher 过去式: matched 过去分词: matched 现在分词: matching 第三人称单数: matches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('saucer', '[\'sɔːsər]', 'n.茶托；碟子', '1. He is drinking with a cup and saucer. 他正在用带茶托的茶杯喝茶。 2. First, Linc pushed over a chair and jolted a knickknack table off its accustomed site hard enough so that a cup and saucer fell to the rug. 第一，林克推翻了一个椅子，把一个放小摆设的小桌子用力的推离了原来的位置，使上面的一个杯子和茶托掉到了地毯上。 3. The cat has upset its saucer of milk. 那只猫打翻了它的牛奶碟子。 4. I think I prefer the round plate and saucer,though. 虽然如此，我想我还是偏好圆形盘子和小碟子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('travel', '[\'trævl]', 'v.旅行；去某地；传播；快速移动；[体]走步 n.旅行；移动', '1. You are hardly fit to travel alone at present. 照目前的情况,你不宜单独旅行。 2. I travel 40 miles to work every day. 我每天奔波40英里去上班。 3. When we speak, sound waves begin to travel in all directions. 我们说话时,声波就开始向四面八方传播扩散。 4. I don\'t know the exact speed of the car, but it was certainly travelling. 我不知道那辆汽车的准确速度,但它确实开得非常快。 5. He met many interesting people in his travels. 旅行中他遇到了许多有趣的人。', '过去式: traveled/travelled 过去分词: traveled/travelled 现在分词: traveling/travelling 第三人称单数: travels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dominant', '[\'dɑːmɪnənt]', 'adj.主要的；占优势的；显性的 n.主宰者；显性基因', '1. Peace was the dominant theme of the conference. 和平是大会的首要议题。 2. He is a dominant leader in our university. 他是我们学校最主要的一位领导。 3. The right hand is dominant in most people. 大多数人的右手是优势手。 4. The company can\'t preserve its dominant position in the market. 该公司在市场上不能让自己保持优势地位。 5. We should be the dominant of ourselves. 我们要做自己的主宰者。', '副词: dominantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interference', '[ˌɪntər\'fɪrəns]', 'n.干扰；妨碍', '1. Her mother\'s interference exacerbated the difficulties in their marriage. 她母亲从中干预使他们的婚姻雪上加霜。 2. Her interference was not warranted. 她干涉得毫无道理。 3. I resented his interference in my affairs. 我很不满他干预我的私事。 4. I can not hear the talk, you see, there\'s so much interference. 我听不见那谈话，你瞧，干扰这么多。', '形容词: interferential');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('butcher', '[\'bʊtʃər]', 'n.屠夫；刽子手；肉商；小贩 vt.屠宰；滥杀；将某事弄得一团糟', '1. The butcher chopped off a rib of frozen pork. 屠夫砍下一块冻肉的肋条。 2. Hitler was as a great a butcher as the world has seen. 希特勒是有史以来最大的侩子手。 3. The butcher will dress the chicken for you. 肉商将为你准备加工好的鸡。 4. The butcher\'s shop stank in hot weather. 肉铺热天散发出腥臭味。 5. Many western countries raise and butcher a large number of beef cattle. 许多西方国家饲养并屠宰大量的肉牛。', '名词: butcherer 过去式: butchered 过去分词: butchered 现在分词: butchering 第三人称单数: butchers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rope', '[roʊp]', 'n.绳索；一串；绞刑 v.捆绑；说服（口）', '1. The rope was not strong enough, so we used wire. 这根绳子不够结实，所以我们用金属线。 2. They tied their prisoner up with a piece of rope. 他们用绳索把犯人捆起来。 3. I bought a beautiful rope of pearls. 我买了一串很好看的珠子。 4. He roped his horse on a nearby tree. 他把马拴到附近的一棵树上。', '名词: roper 过去式: roped 过去分词: roped 现在分词: roping 第三人称单数: ropes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('successive', '[sək\'sesɪv]', 'adj.连续的；接连的；接二连三的', '1. We have had three successive years of good harvest. 我们已连续三年丰收。 2. He dropped the nails on the ground and successive clangs were heard. 他把钉子掉到了地上，听见了一连串的叮当声。 3. Continuity is ensured by using the same props in successive scenes. 在连续的场景中使用同样的道具以确保前后衔接。 4. Andrea paid no attention to the successive charges which were brought against him. 安德烈听着维尔福起诉书中接连提出来的罪名。', '副词: successively 名词: successiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('indulge', '[ɪn\'dʌldʒ]', 'vt.迁就；纵情于；放任 vi.放纵自己于 ...', '1. If you will indulge me for one moment, I think I can explain the matter to you. 你要是容我把话说完,我想我可以把此事给你解释清楚。 2. It pleased me to indulge her wishes. 放手满足她的欲望，使我感到高兴。 3. He no longer indulged himself in smoking. 他不再过度吸烟了。 4. He indulged his children too much. 他太纵容他的孩子们了。 5. I shall forget about dieting today. I\'m just going to indulge. 今天我要把节食计划置之脑后,想吃什么就吃什么。', '名词: indulger 过去式: indulged 过去分词: indulged 现在分词: indulging 第三人称单数: indulges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wax', '[wæks]', 'n.蜡；蜂蜡 vt.(用蜡)涂 vi.变圆', '1. Blobs of wax covered the candlestick. 烛台上全是一团团的蜡。 2. He is modeling a unicorn in wax . 他在用蜡制作独角兽。 3. They bought wax and honey up by the great. 他们大量购进蜜蜡和蜂蜜。 4. Why did she have to wax the floors herself? 她干什么非要自己动手给地板打腊? 5. The moon is waxing. 月亮越来越圆。', '过去式: waxed 过去分词: waxed 现在分词: waxing 第三人称单数: waxes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('imperial', '[ɪm\'pɪriəl]', 'adj.帝国的；皇帝的；特大的；英制的 n.皇帝；女皇；马车车顶；特大号', '1. Imperial sovereignty rests on a mixed constitution. 帝国的主权基于一种复杂的构成。 2. There are many ways to get to the imperial Theater. 到帝国戏院有很多条路。 3. The Palace Museum is the imperial palace of ancient Chinese emperors. 故宫是中国古代皇帝的皇宫。 4. Imperial gardens occupy large areas. 皇家园林占地很广。 5. An imperial edict is a writ in the name of an emperor. 诏书是以皇帝名义发布指令的专用文书。', '副词: imperially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eye', '[aɪ]', 'n.眼睛；目光；视力；观点；鉴赏力 v.看；注视；审视', '1. He could not meet his father\'s eye. 他不敢正视父亲的目光。 2. She reads with a sharp eye for idiom. 她阅读时以敏锐的目光审视语言的习惯用法。 3. He has weak eyes. 他的视力不佳。 4. Reading in the sunlight does harm to your eye sight. 在太阳光下读书对视力有害。 5. Kevin likes to eye every girl who walks by. 凯文喜欢看每一个走过他面前的女孩子。', '过去式: eyed 过去分词: eyed 现在分词: eyeing/eying 第三人称单数: eyes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('organism', '[\'ɔːrɡənɪzəm]', 'n.有机体；生物体；有机组织', '1. Germs may invade the organism. 细菌会侵入有机体。 2. Organism is the basic study of biology. 生物体是生物研究的基础领域。 3. The ameba is a very simple organism. 变形虫是很简单的生物体。 4. An organism adapts best when stresses are slightly increased. 当压力被稍微地提高时，是生物体适应的最好状况。', '形容词: organismal 副词: organismically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suggestion', '[sə\'dʒestʃən]', 'n.建议；意见；有...迹象；联想', '1. What a ridiculous suggestion! 多么荒唐的建议！ 2. I put the computer over there at your suggestion. 根据你的建议，我把计算机放在那边了。 3. Can you give me any suggestion on this matter? 关于这件事，你能给我一些建议吗？ 4. He will indignantly repudiate the suggestion. 他会气愤地拒绝接受这一意见。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('goodness', '[\'ɡʊdnəs]', 'n.善良；美德；精华 int.天哪', '1. He keeps extolling her goodness. 他对她的善良赞不绝口。 2. Does goodness charm more than beauty? 善良是否比美色更为人们所欣赏？ 3. She\'s the very incarnation of goodness. 她是美德的化身。 4. Goodness often charms more than mere beauty. 美德比徒具美貌更迷人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lapse', '[læps]', 'n.过失；流逝；间隔；堕落；失效 vi.流逝；失效；堕落；停止 vt.使失效', '1. The man admitted driving over the speed limit and apologized for the lapse. 这名男子承认超速行驶,并且为自己的过失道歉。 2. I started to eat the peas with my hands, but I don\'t think anyone noticed my little lapse. 我开始用手吃豌豆，但我想没有人注意到我的小错误。 3. The lapse of time is irreversible. 时光流逝不可逆转。 4. The lapse of year will never efface that scene of ruin from my memory. 时光的流逝绝不会把那废墟的景象从我的记忆中冲淡。 5. The days lapsed away. 日子在不知不觉之中过去。', '名词: lapser 过去式: lapsed 过去分词: lapsed 现在分词: lapsing 第三人称单数: lapses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('criticism', '[\'krɪtɪsɪzəm]', 'n.批评；评论', '1. He is impervious to criticism. 他对批评我行我素。 2. His behavior called forth sharp criticism. 他的行为招致尖锐的批评。 3. Such a questionable assertion is sure to provoke criticism. 这种有问题的主张肯定会招致非议。 4. I don\'t like to read his literary criticism. 我不喜欢读他的文学批评。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('monopoly', '[mə\'nɑːpəli]', 'n.垄断；独占；专利；控制', '1. Liberty and monopoly cannot live together. 自由与垄断不能并存。 2. The company will become a state-owned monopoly. 这家企业将变成一家国有的垄断企业。 3. Imperialism is the monopoly stage of capitalism. 帝国主义是资本主义的垄断阶段。 4. The government has a monopoly of oil production in that country. 在那个国家，政府独占石油开采权。', '形容词: monopolistic 副词: monopolistically 名词: monopolism 名词复数: monopolies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shot', '[ʃɑːt]', 'n.注射；投篮；发射；拍摄；开枪；子弹 adj.(织物)闪色的；精疲力尽的；完了的 动词shoot的过去式和过去分词.', '1. He gave me a second shot of penicillin. 他又给我打了一针青霉素。 2. Eight-year-old Griffin Stevens made the shot of a lifetime this past weekend. 8岁的格里芬史蒂文斯在本周末创造了一次一生难忘的投篮。 3. In this case, the ever-changing waves are part of our shot. 在本例中,不断变化的波浪也是我们拍摄的一部分内容。 4. I heard a shot in his room. 我听到他的房间内一声枪响。 5. I\'m shot. I\'m too old for this job. 我一点力气都没有了，我这岁数干不动这活儿了。', '过去式: shotted 过去分词: shotted 现在分词: shotting 第三人称单数: shots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('political', '[pə\'lɪtɪkl]', 'adj.政治的；政治上的；政党的；人事的；争权夺利的', '1. He has some pretty strange political ideas. 他有一些很奇怪的政治信念。 2. She entered the political arena after her husband\'s death. 她丈夫死后，她进入了政界。 3. The British political system has evolved over several centuries. 英国的政治制度是经过几个世纪逐步发展而成的。 4. The program of a political party is a banner. 一个政党的纲领就是一面旗帜。', '副词: politically 名词: politicalization 动词: politicalize');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mother', '[\'mʌðər]', 'n.母亲；妈妈 adj.母亲的；母体的；本源的 vt.生育；像母亲一样关爱', '1. I wonder when mother will ring? 我不知道母亲什么时候会打电话来？ 2. It happened that my mother was out that day. 我母亲恰巧那天出去了。 3. He disobeyed his mother and went to the party. 他不听母亲的劝告，参加了那次聚会。 4. My mother is a housewife. 我妈妈是个家庭妇女。 5. Mother love is the greatest in the world. 世界上母爱是最伟大的。 6. My sister mothered a little baby two days ago. 两天前我姐姐生了个孩子。', '过去式: mothered 过去分词: mothered 现在分词: mothering 第三人称单数: mothers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blur', '[blɜːr]', 'v.弄脏；使 ... 模糊 n.污点；模糊', '1. The damp paper caused the ink to blur. 潮纸因墨水弄上污渍。 2. Don\'t blur the distinctions between things. 不要模糊事物之间的差别。 3. Do drunkards blur reality, or come closer to it? 酒醉之后是使现实模糊不清，还是更加接近现实了呢? 4. But we see it only as a hazy blur. 但我们看到的只是模糊的斑点。', '形容词: blurry 名词: blurriness 过去式: blurred 过去分词: blurred 现在分词: blurring 第三人称单数: blurs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suggest', '[sə\'dʒest]', 'vt.建议；暗示；使想起；表明；要求', '1. I suggested going for a walk. 我建议去散步。 2. I suggested to him that we should tackle the problem another way. 我向他建议我们用另一种方式处理这个问题。 3. He had the effrontery to suggest that she enjoyed being unhappy. 他无耻地大胆暗示，她喜欢不幸。 4. The thought of summer suggests swimming. 想到夏天，就使人联想到游泳。', '名词: suggester 过去式: suggested 过去分词: suggested 现在分词: suggesting 第三人称单数: suggests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('advisable', '[əd\'vaɪzəbl]', 'adj.明智的；可取的', '1. It is advisable to be forearmed. 预作准备是明智的。 2. This line of conduct seems advisable to me. 这一行动方针对我来说似乎是很可取的。 3. It is not advisable just to work away without making a timely summing-up of experience. 一味埋头干下去不做及时的经验总结是不可取的。', '副词: advisably 名词: advisability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('limit', '[\'lɪmɪt]', 'n.限度；限制；界限 vt.限制；限定', '1. Her ambition knows no limit. 她的野心没有限度。 2. I\'ll help as much as I can, but there is a limit to what I can do. 我会尽力帮忙，但我所能做的也是有限度的。 3. His speech ran over the time limit. 他的讲话超过了规定的时间限制。 4. That fence is the limit of the schoolyard. 那堵围墙是校园的界限。 5. We must limit our spending. 我们必须限制我们的开支。', '形容词: limitable 过去式: limited 过去分词: limited 现在分词: limiting 第三人称单数: limits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plague', '[pleɪɡ]', 'n.瘟疫；麻烦；灾祸 vt.折磨；烦扰；造成麻烦', '1. Plague came in the wake of earthquake. 地震之后紧跟着就是瘟疫。 2. A great plague was then raging in the city. 那时一场大瘟疫正在该城肆虐。 3. He\'s been avoiding me like the plague since our quarrel. 我们吵架以後，他一直如避蛇蝎似的躲著我。 4. A plague of locusts affected the harvest a lot this year. 蝗灾大大影响了今年的丰收。 5. A demon or spirit once was thought to plague sleeping people. 梦魔被认为折磨睡觉的人的魔鬼或灵魂', '名词: plaguer 过去式: plagued 过去分词: plagued 现在分词: plaguing 第三人称单数: plagues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('concede', '[kən\'siːd]', 'vt.承认；给予；让步；认输 vi.让步', '1. I concede that you are right. 我承认你是对的。 2. You must concede that I have tried my best. 你必须承认我已经尽力了。 3. The defeated side had to concede some of their territory to the enemy. 战败的一方不得不把一部分领土割让给了敌人。 4. You concede nothing to me and I have to concede everything to you. 你对我无论什么都不肯让步；我对你，可无论什么都得让步。 5. Mike had to concede when he confronted his parents 当面对他的父母,麦克不得不让步。', '副词: concededly 名词: conceder 过去式: conceded 过去分词: conceded 现在分词: conceding 第三人称单数: concedes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unique', '[ju\'niːk]', 'adj.独特的；独一无二的；稀罕的', '1. He occupies a unique place in English literature. 他在英国文学中占有独特的地位。 2. The elephant\'s trunk is a unique form of appendage. 象的鼻子是一种独特的附肢。 3. It\'s a unique work of art. 这是独一无二的艺术作品。 4. The custom is unique to the region. 这种风俗是这一地区特有的。', '副词: uniquely 名词: uniqueness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('luggage', '[\'lʌɡɪdʒ]', 'n.行李', '1. All the luggage has been strapped up. 所有行李都已捆扎好。 2. He put his bag on the luggage rack. 他把包放在行李架上。 3. The porter was weighed down by all the luggage. 搬运工扛着这些行李压得直不起腰来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chicken', '[\'tʃɪkɪn]', 'n.鸡；鸡肉；胆小者 adj.懦弱的；胆小的 vi.失去勇气', '1. He has a chicken farm. 他有一个养鸡场。 2. He is mending the wire mesh in front of the chicken coop. 他正在鸡笼前面修理铁丝网。 3. This soup tastes of chicken. 这汤里有鸡肉的味道。 4. There was fried chicken for dinner. 有炸鸡肉作晚餐。 5. I was terrified, but I didn\'t want the others to think I was chicken. 我很害怕,但是我不想其他人认为我很怯懦。 6. The boy chickened out of climbing up the tree. 男孩胆怯了,不敢爬上这棵树。', '过去式: chickened 过去分词: chickened 现在分词: chickening 第三人称单数: chickens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Bible', '[\'baɪbl]', 'n.圣经；（b~）有权威的书', '1. You can find this sentence in the Holy Bible. 你可以在圣经上找到这句话。 2. He quotes the Bible to support his belief. 他引述圣经以支持自己的信条。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('author', '[\'ɔːθər]', 'n.作家；作者 vt.编写；创作 Author. n.上帝', '1. This book shows that he is an ingenious author. 这本书表明他是一个有创造力的作家。 2. The book was translated without the sanction of the author. 这本书未经作者许可就给翻译了。 3. The book is authored by six leading historians. 这本书由六名权威的历史学家编写而成。 4. He authored two best-sellers. 他写过两部畅销书。 5. God is the author and approver of sin, for sin is the accomplishment of His will. 上帝是罪的始创者，罪既然成就上帝的旨意，因此是上帝喜悦的。', '形容词: authorial 过去式: authored 过去分词: authored 现在分词: authoring 第三人称单数: authors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mode', '[moʊd]', 'n.方式；模式；样式；风格', '1. The country girl was not used to their lavish mode of living. 这个乡下姑娘不习惯他们奢侈的生活方式。 2. The spacecraft was in its recovery mode. 这艘飞船处于返回状态。 3. Her new dress is the latest mode in this season. 她的新连衣裙是这一季最新的款式。 4. He has no intention of changing his mode of attire. 他没有意愿去改变自己穿着的风格。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('child', '[tʃaɪld]', 'n.小孩；子女；产物', '1. He\'s still but a child. 他仅仅是个小孩子。 2. He tutored the child in physics. 他给这小孩辅导物理。 3. They cherished the child as one of their own. 他们把这孩子当作自己亲生子女一般。 4. Every child bares the responsibility and obligation of supporting the old. 每位子女都负有赡养老人的责任和义务。', '形容词: childless 名词: childlessness 名词复数: children');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cancer', '[\'kænsər]', 'n.癌；肿瘤；毒瘤 Cancer. n.巨蟹座', '1. He was afflicted with cancer. 他患了癌症。 2. The patient finally died from cancer. 那位病人最终死于癌症。 3. He\'s got a cancer in his liver. 他得了肝癌。 4. The oncologist invented a new kind of interferon to prevent cancer. 那位肿瘤学家发明了一种可以预防癌症的干扰素。 5. I\'m a Cancer and my brother is a Leo. 我是巨蟹座，弟弟是狮子座。', '形容词: cancerous');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gaze', '[ɡeɪz]', 'vi.凝视 n.凝视', '1. She sat gazing out of the window. 她坐着凝视着窗外。 2. He gaze ruefully in the mirror at his greying lock. 他凝视著镜中自己日见花白的头发，感慨岁月不待人。 3. She gazed at me in disbelief when I told her the news. 我告诉她这消息时，她以怀疑的目光注视著我。 4. Your intent gaze made her uncomfortable. 你的注目凝视使她感到不自在。', '名词: gazer 过去式: gazed 过去分词: gazed 现在分词: gazing 第三人称单数: gazes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soap', '[soʊp]', 'n.肥皂；肥皂剧 vt.用肥皂洗；阿谀奉承', '1. The soap slipped out of my hand. 肥皂从我手上滑落了。 2. Tallow can be used for making soap. 动物脂可以用来做香皂。 3. I only caught the end of the soap opera. 我只看到了肥皂剧的结尾。 4. This club was beginning to seem like a soap opera. 这个社团开始就像一出肥皂剧。 5. Is it good to soap the baby down each time? 每次都把婴孩身上打上肥皂好吗？', '过去式: soaped 过去分词: soaped 现在分词: soaping 第三人称单数: soaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comrade', '[\'kɑːmræd]', 'n.同志', '1. He puts me in mind of a comrade in my army unit. 他使我想起了我们部队的一位同志。 2. Comrade Lei Feng left an undying example behind. 雷锋同志留下了一个不朽的榜样。', '名词: comradeship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ultimate', '[\'ʌltɪmət]', 'adj.根本的；极限的；最后的；终极的 n.终极；极品；根本', '1. Hard work is the ultimate source of success. 努力工作是成功之本。 2. This had been an ultimate issue. 这个问题是个原则性的问题。 3. GUPTA And the Ironman is the ultimate competition. 甘普塔铁人是一个极限的竞争。 4. I believe that I will bring my ultimate competitiveness in the advanced business management into full play with the guidance of professional teachers. 我认为在精英的师资力量的指导下我将在高级商业管理方面发挥我极限的竞争力。 5. Such behavior is the ultimate in idiocy. 这样的行为愚蠢透顶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conjunction', '[kən\'dʒʌŋkʃn]', 'n.结合；关联；连词；(事件等的)同时发生', '1. The novel should be read in conjunction with the author\'s biography. 这本小说应该和作者传记一起读。 2. The conjunction of workmanship and artistry in making jewelry decides the value of the jewelry. 在珠宝饰物的制造中，手工与艺术的结合决定了珠宝的价值。 3. The word is a temporal conjunction. 该词是表示时间的连词。 4. An unusual conjunction of circumstances led to the incident. 各种情况的偶然巧合导致了这件事的发生。', '形容词: conjunctional 副词: conjunctionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('database', '[\'deɪtəbeɪs]', 'n.数据库', '1. Can you set up a database? 你能建一个数据库吗? 2. This database is only accessible by the authorized manager. 只有授权的管理员才可以访问此数据库。 3. The database is updated monthly. 数据库每月更新。 4. The information is stored on a large database. 信息储存在巨大的数据库中。', '过去式: databased 过去分词: databased 现在分词: databasing 第三人称单数: databases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('calcium', '[\'kælsiəm]', 'n.钙', '1. We need some calcium everyday. 我们每天需要些钙。 2. I have a slight calcium deficiency. 我有点缺钙。 3. Like most dairy products, such as milk and cheese, yogurt contains a lot of calcium. 像大部分的乳制品，如牛奶和奶酪一样，优酪乳含有许多钙质。', '简写符号: Ca');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('project', '[\'prɑːdʒekt]', 'n.计划；工程；项目；课题；专题研究；住房工程 v.计划；预计；设计；放映；投射；表达；突出；投掷', '1. Our project was scrubbed. 我们的计划被取消了。 2. They doubted of the feasibility of the project. 他们怀疑这个计划的可行性。 3. The project is proceeding as planned. 工程正在按计划进行。 4. We are discussing the project to establish a new national park 我们正在讨论建立一个新的国家公园的工程。 5. The government projected a tax decrease. 政府计划降低税收。', '形容词: projectable');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('isle', '[aɪl]', 'n.岛；群岛', '1. The tiny isle had a sandy beach. 这小岛有一片沙滩。 2. In a word, the isle was inhabited. 总而言之，这个小岛上确是有居民的。 3. This isle was then floating and unstable. 这座小岛漂浮在水面上并且不稳定。 4. Horses would not have been lacking in the Isle of Wight. 在怀特岛上，马匹是不可或缺的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('await', '[ə\'weɪt]', 'v.等候；期待；将降临于', '1. We await your shipping instructions. 我们等候你们的装船指示。 2. I am awaiting their reply. 我正在等待他们的答复。 3. We eagerly await your early arrival. 我们殷切地期待你早日光临。 4. A warm welcome awaits you. 你将受到热烈的欢迎。', '过去式: awaited 过去分词: awaited 现在分词: awaiting 第三人称单数: awaits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obedient', '[ə\'biːdiənt]', 'adj.服从的；顺从的', '1. I was no longer a sweet obedient little boy. 我不再是一个可爱的顺从的小男孩。 2. She is an obedient girl and always obeys her parents. 她是个顺从的孩子，总是服从父母。', '副词: obediently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ministry', '[\'mɪnɪstri]', 'n.(政府的)部；内阁；(全体)牧师', '1. She\'s on attachment to the Ministry of Defense. 她现在隶属于国防部。 2. The army, navy and airforce are all controlled by the Ministry of Defense. 陆海空军皆由国防部控制。 3. The Ministry released him on compassionate grounds. 内阁因同情而将他释放。 4. The ministry is about to haul up the white flag. 该内阁正准备认输。', '名词复数: ministries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sun', '[sʌn]', 'n.太阳；阳光；中心人物 v.晒太阳', '1. The earth goes round the sun. 地球绕着太阳运行。 2. The sun rises in the east. 太阳从东方升起。 3. They sat in the sun roasting themselves. 他们坐着晒太阳。 4. The diamond shone with every hue under the sun. 这颗钻石在阳光下显得色彩斑斓。 5. Do you like to sun yourself on the beach? 你想去海滩晒太阳吗?', '过去式: sunned 过去分词: sunned 现在分词: sunning 第三人称单数: suns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thermometer', '[θər\'mɑːmɪtər]', 'n.温度计', '1. The thermometer reads 27 degrees. 温度计的读数是27度。 2. The thermometer fell to zero lastnight. 昨夜温度计显示气温下降到零度。 3. The readings on my thermometer last month were well above the average. 我的温度计上个月的读数远远超过平均温度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forecast', '[\'fɔːrkæst]', 'n.预测；预报 v.预测', '1. Share prices plunged as a result of the gloomy economic forecast. 关于经济前景暗淡的预测导致股票价格大跌。 2. The Treasury\'s forecast assumes that inflation will remain below 3%. 财政部的预测称,通货膨胀率将保持在3%25以下。 3. The weather forecast says it will be sunny tomorrow. 天气预报说明天是晴天。 4. Despite the good weather forecast, the next morning was as wet as ever. 尽管预报称天气很好，但次日上午仍阴雨绵绵。 5. They tried to forecast the result of the football match. 他们试图预测这场足球比赛的结果。', '形容词: forecastable 名词: forecaster 过去式: forecast/forecasted 过去分词: forecast/forecasted 现在分词: forecasting 第三人称单数: forecasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grain', '[ɡreɪn]', 'n.谷物；谷类；微量；颗粒；纹理；格令 v.形成(颗粒)；(用谷物)喂养', '1. We ship grain to Africa. 我们把谷物运往非洲。 2. There are a few grains of rice in a bowl. 碗中有几颗米粒。 3. There isn\'t a grain of truth in it. 那事无丝毫真实性。 4. The coffee was good, but thick with grains. 咖啡很好, 但满是粒子。 5. Physical isolation goes against the corporate grain, the hierarchy being organized around the office. 身体上的隔绝违反合作意愿，使办公室周围形成特定阶层。', '名词: grainer 过去式: grained 过去分词: grained 现在分词: graining 第三人称单数: grains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inquiry', '[ɪn\'kwaɪrɪ]', 'n.调查；询问；打听；查问 =enquiry(英).', '1. We made an application to the court for an inquiry. 我们曾请求法院调查。 2. They\'ve promised a thorough inquiry into the plane crash. 他们答应对这次飞机失事进行彻底的调查。 3. I\'m not able to help you with your inquiry. 我对你的咨询无能为力。 4. He is fishing for information by a letter of inquiry. 他写信询问，希望打听一下消息。', '异体字: enquiry 名词复数: inquiries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('perfection', '[pər\'fekʃn]', 'n.完美；完善', '1. The design approximates perfection. 这个设计几乎是完美的。 2. As an actress, she is perfection itself. 作为一名女演员，她是完美的典型。 3. Incomplete beauty is the perfection. 不完善的美，就是完美。 4. Our style is distinctive and our goal is perfection! 与众不同是我们的风格，追求完善是我们的宗旨！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('starve', '[stɑːrv]', 'vi.挨饿；受饿；极度匮乏 vt.使挨饿；使饿死', '1. They were suffered to starve on the pavement. 他们流流街头，忍饥挨饿。 2. They would starve if food was difficult to find. 如果很难找到食物，他们就会挨饿。 3. They would rather starve than give way. 他们宁愿饿死也不妥协。 4. The explorers starved to death in the desert. 探险者们在沙漠中饿死了。 5. It is silly to starve yourself to be skinny. 显得有骨感而挨饿是愚蠢的.', '过去式: starved 过去分词: starved 现在分词: starving 第三人称单数: starves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soul', '[soʊl]', 'n.灵魂；心灵；精神', '1. Creativity is the soul of a nation. 创新是一个民族进步的灵魂。 2. No words can express the secret agony of my soul. 没有任何语言能够表达我心灵中的隐痛。 3. The eye is the window of the soul. 眼睛是心灵的窗户。 4. Knowledge is the food of the soul. 知识是精神食粮。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('identity', '[aɪ\'dentəti]', 'n.一致；身份；特征', '1. Identity of interests is the bond that unites them. 利害的一致是把他们联合起来的纽带。 2. The police asked him to show his identity card. 警察让他出示身份证。 3. The journalist did not want to reveal the identity of his informant. 那个新闻工作者不想透露消息提供人的身分。 4. He had to make his identity public. 他不得不公开自己的身份。', '名词复数: identities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('step', '[step]', 'n.步骤；台阶；舞步；步伐 v.踏；以步测量', '1. The government is taking steps to control the rising crime rate. 政府正采取措施以控制不断上升的犯罪率。 2. We should take steps to prevent war. 我们应当采取措施制止战争。 3. However, the next step can be started. 然而,下一步骤可以开始。 4. They are not attached to the fruits of karma, and are but one step from Buddhahood. 他们不附上因果报应的果实,而只是成佛的一个台阶。 5. She stepped on a loose stone and twisted her ankle. 她踩到一块松动的石头上，扭伤了脚踝。', '过去式: stepped 过去分词: stepped 现在分词: stepping 第三人称单数: steps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('harden', '[\'hɑːrdn]', 'v.(使)变硬；(使)坚强', '1. They harden clay by putting it in a fire. 他们把粘土坯放在炉火里使其变硬。 2. The varnish takes a few minutes to harden. 清漆几分钟就能变硬。 3. Missus Lederer later said that one Sun-Times editor helped her harden herself to those stories. 莱德尔太太后来说，有一位晨报的编辑帮助她，让她面对这些信件而变得坚强。 4. Hardship can harden your will. 艰难困苦可以使你意志坚强。', '过去式: hardened 过去分词: hardened 现在分词: hardening 第三人称单数: hardens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('headquarters', '[\'hedkwɔːrtərz]', 'n.总部；司令部；指挥部', '1. The company\'s headquarters is based in London. 这家公司的总部设在伦敦。 2. She tapped out in code to headquarters. 她给总部发出密码电报。 3. The soldier reported to headquarters. 这个士兵向司令部作了报告。 4. We lost no time in returning to the headquarters. 我们赶紧回到指挥部。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('monarch', '[\'mɑːnərk]', 'n.帝王；统治者；君主 n.君王斑点蝶', '1. They attempted to overthrow the monarch. 他们企图推翻国王。 2. The national band played for the visiting monarch. 国家乐团演奏给来访的帝王听。 3. I think myself happier now than the greatest monarch upon earth. 我觉得这个时候比世界上什么帝王都快乐。 4. They also crowned Dath\'Remar as their first monarch. 他们拥护达斯雷玛成为他们的第一任皇权统治者。 5. I saw the monarch butterfly by accident. 我偶尔看见了君王斑点蝶。', '形容词: monarchal 副词: monarchally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('passage', '[\'pæsɪdʒ]', 'n.通过；通道；走廊；(文章等的)段落；(时间的)消逝', '1. The bridge is not strong enough to allow the passage of vehicles. 这座桥不够牢固，车辆不能通行。 2. The police kept a clear passage for the traffic. 警方使来往车辆畅通无阻。 3. We discovered a secret passage behind the wall. 我们在墙后发现了一个秘密通道。 4. This is our room, and yours is down the passage. 这是我们的房间，你们的在走廊的那一头。', '过去式: passaged 过去分词: passaged 现在分词: passaging 第三人称单数: passages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('captain', '[\'kæptɪn]', 'n.首领；队长；船长 vt.指挥；率领', '1. And they\'ll find that their bold captain is nowhere to be found 但他们再也找不到他们豪勇的首领了。 2. The captain led our team to victory. 队长带领我们队取得了胜利。 3. The football captain was the mogul of the school. 那足球队长是该校的大人物。 4. The captain bawled out an order to his soldiers. 队长向士兵们大声发出命令。 5. Strong leadership is needed to captain the team. 担任这个队的队长需要强有力的领导才能。', '名词: captaincy 过去式: captained 过去分词: captained 现在分词: captaining 第三人称单数: captains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lake', '[leɪk]', 'n.湖；湖泊 n.深红色；[化]色淀', '1. He fell into the lake. 他掉进了湖里。 2. The garden reaches the lake. 花园一直延伸到湖边。 3. We crossed the lake in a canoe. 我们乘独木舟过河。 4. I reached the gate that opened towards the lake. 我走到临湖而开的那扇门前。 5. I\'ve just run out of crimson lake paint. 我正好用完了胭脂红色的颜料。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('framework', '[\'freɪmwɜːrk]', 'n.框架；体系；结构', '1. They established a basic framework of ground rules for discussions. 他们建立了讨论的基本准则的基本框架。 2. Government is the one who establishes national policy framework. 国家政策体系的是由政府建立的。 3. It\'s a bridge of steel framework. 那是座钢铁结构的桥梁。 4. All the cases can be considered within the framework of the existing rules. 一切情况都可依据现行章程的结构加以考虑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('foremost', '[\'fɔːrmoʊst]', 'adj.最重要的；最初的 adv.在最前面', '1. He is one of the foremost scientists in China. 他是中国最重要的科学家之一。 2. He was one of the foremost literary scholars in England. 他是英格兰最重要的文学专家之一。 3. Good schemes will do more than funnel money from latecomers to early takers, allowing the foremost to prosper at the expense of the hindmost. 好的庞式计划将不仅仅是将钱从后来者转到早的加入者手中，以最后面的加入者为代价来使最初的加入者获得成功。 4. First and foremost, I think you should work harder on your biology. 首先，我认为你应该多在生物学上下功夫。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blow', '[bloʊ]', 'n.打击；殴打；吹 v.吹；风吹；擤(鼻子)；(保险丝)熔断；<口>浪费(机会)', '1. The death of their daughter was a cruel blow. 女儿的死对他们是一个残酷的打击。 2. I was dazed by the blow on my head. 我的头挨了一击而觉得晕眩。 3. Bill knocked him down with one blow. 比尔一拳把他打倒在地。 4. Now, Peter, make a wish and blow out the candles. 彼得,现在你许个愿,然后吹蜡烛。', '过去式: blew 过去分词: blown 现在分词: blowing 第三人称单数: blows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compensate', '[\'kɑːmpenseɪt]', 'v.补偿；赔偿；付报酬', '1. Nothing can compensate for the loss of one\'s health. 什么都不能补偿健康受损。 2. She was compensated by the insurance company for her injuries. 她受伤后获得保险公司的赔偿。 3. You will have to compensate us for the loss. 你必须赔偿我们的损失。', '形容词: compensative 名词: compensator 过去式: compensated 过去分词: compensated 现在分词: compensating 第三人称单数: compensates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('genius', '[\'dʒiːniəs]', 'n.天才；天赋', '1. He makes much account of her musical genius. 他重视她的音乐天才。 2. He is a mathematical genius. 他是一个数学天才。 3. Einstein was a mathematical genius. 爱因斯坦是数学天才。 4. His genius as a painter flowered very early. 他的绘画天赋很早就发挥出来。', '名词复数: geniuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chocolate', '[\'tʃɑːklət]', 'n.巧克力；巧克力糖；巧克力色 adj.巧克力的；巧克力色的', '1. Never eat chocolate before dinner. 饭前不要吃巧克力。 2. Would you like a cup of chocolate? 你想要杯巧克力饮料吗？ 3. The boy spent 10 pennies on chocolate. 这男孩花了10便士买巧克力糖。 4. She dealt out a bar of chocolate to each child. 她分给每个孩子一块巧克力糖。 5. We soon despatched the chocolate cake. 我们很快就吃完了巧克力蛋糕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enthusiasm', '[ɪn\'θuːziæzəm]', 'n.热情；热心；热衷的事物', '1. His refusal iced our enthusiasm. 他的拒绝浇熄了我们的热情。 2. She seemed lacking in enthusiasm when we were talking about that film. 我们谈论那部电影时,她看来好像没多大热情。 3. His enthusiasm made everyone else interested. 他的热心激发了大家的兴致。 4. One of my great enthusiasms is music. 我的一大爱好就是音乐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crude', '[kruːd]', 'adj.天然的；未加工的；粗鲁的；粗糙的；简陋的 n.原油；天然的物质', '1. China is a country rich in crude oil. 中国是一个原油丰富的国家。 2. The price of crude oil has come down recently. 最近原油的价格已经下降了。 3. This crude glycerin is from pure virgin vegetable oil. 这是未加工的甘油，来自纯洁，原始的植物油。 4. It was crude of him to say that. 他那样说太粗鲁了。 5. In fact, a speciality crude is suitable only for bitumen production. 事实上，这种特性的原油只适宜于生产沥青。', '副词: crudely 比较级: cruder 最高级: crudest 名词: crudity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pinch', '[pɪntʃ]', 'n.捏；少量；一撮；困苦；<俚>偷窃 v.掐；夹痛；使困苦；<俚>偷窃；逮捕', '1. She gave him a painful pinch. 她捏得他很痛。 2. He put a pinch of salt on his food. 他在自己的食物上撒了一撮盐。 3. Even the town council is now feeling the pinch. 连市政府目前都感到经费困难。 4. He decided to pinch back the buds on the plant. 他决定将植物上的芽掐掉。', '过去式: pinched 过去分词: pinched 现在分词: pinching 第三人称单数: pinches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('academic', '[ˌækə\'demɪk]', 'adj.学院的；学术的；理论的 n.大学教师，大学生；学者，学究', '1. Sir Lawrence Alma-Tadema was an English painter in the academic tradition. 阿尔玛·台德玛是学院派的英国画家。 2. With my strong academic background, I am competent. 依我良好的学术背景,我能胜任。 3. Applicant must possess good conduct and obtain satisfactory academic results. 申请者必须拥有良好品性,并考获令人满意的成绩; 4. During the past four years I have had a good deal of academic experience in communications technology. 四年来,我掌握了丰富的通信技术上的理论知识。', '副词: academically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conceive', '[kən\'siːv]', 'v.设想；想出；怀孕', '1. I cannot conceive of him as a genius. 我不能设想他会是一个天才。 2. I cannot conceive that he would wish to harm us. 我不能想像他会伤害我们。 3. I can not conceive of anything funnier than that . 我想不出有比那更有趣的东西。 4. She was told she couldn\'t conceive. 她得知自己不能怀孕。', '形容词: conceivable 副词: conceivably 名词: conceivability 过去式: conceived 过去分词: conceived 现在分词: conceiving 第三人称单数: conceives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ship', '[ʃɪp]', 'n.船；舰 v.装运；(用船)运送；上(船)；乘(船)', '1. The ship was due to sail the following morning. 这艘船定于第二天启航。 2. A terrible storm forced the ship to put back. 可怕的风暴迫使这条船返航了。 3. The paint on the ship\'s sides was coming off. 舰壳两边的漆开始脱落。 4. Please inform us when we should ship the goods. 请通知我们什么时候装运货物。', '过去式: shipped 过去分词: shipped 现在分词: shipping 第三人称单数: ships');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('harsh', '[hɑːrʃ]', 'adj.粗糙的；严厉的，严酷的；刺耳的；使人不舒服的；大约的', '1. Yorke himself has a harsh face. 约克本人长着张粗糙的脸。 2. The punishment was too harsh for him. 这种惩罚对他来说太严厉了。 3. He had deliberately made his voice harsh. 他故意嘶哑着嗓门。', '副词: harshly 比较级: harsher 最高级: harshest 名词: harshness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glide', '[ɡlaɪd]', 'v.滑动；滑翔；溜走 n.滑动；滑过；滑音', '1. The figure skater glided gracefully over the ice. 花样滑冰者在冰上优雅地滑行。 2. The swans glide gracefully on the lake. 天鹅在湖的上空优美地滑翔。 3. The plane managed to glide down to the runway. 飞机终于成功地滑翔降落在跑道上。 4. He glide away from the classroom. 他溜出教室。 5. When a word ends in a vowel sound and the next word begins with a vowel sound, they are connected with a glide between the two vowels. 如果一个单词以元音结束，下一个单词以元音开始的话，两个元音之间用一个滑音连在一起。', '过去式: glided 过去分词: glided 现在分词: gliding 第三人称单数: glides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('analogy', '[ə\'nælədʒi]', 'n.类比；相似；类似', '1. It is not always reliable to argue by analogy. 用类推法论证并不总是可靠的。 2. He offers an analogy to explain how it works. 他用一个类比来解释这个过程。 3. He drew this conclusion on the analogy of yours. 他根据你的理论类推得出这个结论。 4. No analogy exists between you and me. 你和我之间没有相似之处。', '名词复数: analogies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('so-called', '[soʊ kɔːld]', 'adj.<贬>号称的；所谓的', '1. There is no so-called \"recipe for success\". 所谓“成功的诀窍”是不存在的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cheap', '[tʃiːp]', 'adj.便宜的；廉价的', '1. Her shoes look cheap. 她的那双鞋看上去很便宜。 2. I am going to buy something cheap. 我要买些便宜的东西。 3. A flood of cheap imports has come into the shops. 大量廉价进口商品涌入商店。 4. These are cheap and gaudy clothes. 这是些廉价而花哨的衣服。', '副词: cheaply 比较级: cheaper 最高级: cheapest 名词: cheapness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('estate', '[ɪ\'steɪt]', 'n.财产；遗产；房地产；状态；庄园', '1. The residue of estate belongs to his son. 剩余财产属于他的儿子。 2. He settled part of his estate on his son. 他把部分财产转让给儿子了。 3. The old man left an estate of two million dollars when he died. 那老人去世时留下二百万美元的遗产。 4. He owns a large estate in Scotland. 他在苏格兰有大量地产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weapon', '[\'wepən]', 'n.武器；兵器', '1. This weapon fires anti-aircraft missiles. 这种武器是发射防空导弹的。 2. The fisher used a spear as his weapon. 渔夫用矛作为武器。 3. Whether a gun is a weapon of offence or a weapon of defense depends on which end of it you are at. 枪是攻击武器还是防御武器，要看你的目的而定。 4. Logic is her weapon. 逻辑是她的利器。', '过去式: weaponed 过去分词: weaponed 现在分词: weaponing 第三人称单数: weapons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grant', '[ɡrænt]', 'v.授予；同意；承认；认为 n.授予物；补助金；同意；给予；财产转让 Grant. n.格兰特(男名)', '1. Visa exemption does not grant the right to work. 豁免签证并不授予工作的权利。 2. We grant the truth of what you said. 我们同意你说的是事实。 3. I grant that your explanation is reasonable. 我承认你的解释是合理的。 4. I take it for granted you have read this book. 我认为你一定读过这本书。', '形容词: grantable 名词: granter 过去式: granted 过去分词: granted 现在分词: granting 第三人称单数: grants');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('December', '[dɪ\'sembər]', 'n.十二月', '1. The weather in early December was bleak and unpleasant. 十二月初的天气又阴冷又难受。 2. My little daughter was born in December. 我的小女儿是十二月出生的。 3. December is the last month of the year. 十二月是一年的最后一个月份。 4. Postal applications must be received by 12 December. 邮寄的申请书须于12月12日以前寄达。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evil', '[\'iːvl]', 'adj.邪恶的；有害的；讨厌的 n.邪恶；罪恶；灾祸', '1. His evil designs were frustrated. 他的罪恶企图未能得逞。 2. The book gives, as it were, a picture of the evil old society. 这本书可谓是展现过去那个邪恶社会的图画。 3. Drug dealer is evil to the society. 毒品交易者有害社会。 4. What an evil smell! 多么臭的气味！ 5. My father taught me to render good for evil. 我父亲教导我要以德报怨。', '副词: evilly 比较级: eviler 最高级: evilest 名词: evilness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('terrible', '[\'terəbl]', 'adj.可怕的；极度的；糟糕的', '1. The earthquake was a terrible catastrophe. 这次地震是个可怕的灾难。 2. If they had any respect for human life they wouldn\'t do such terrible things. 他们如果还顾及人的生命就不会做出这样可怕的事来。 3. The government didn\'t allow reporting the terrible accident. 政府不允许报道那起严重事故。 4. What terrible weather! 多坏的天气。', '副词: terribly 名词: terribleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('proper', '[\'prɑːpər]', 'adj.合适的；正当的；真正的', '1. He could not come up with a proper answer. 他想不出一个合适的回答。 2. It\'s not proper for you to catch him up very short. 你突然打断他的话是不恰当的。 3. The company does not take proper fire precaution. 公司未采取正当的防火措施。 4. She hadn\'t had a proper holiday for years. 多年来她都没有过真正的假期。', '副词: properly 名词: properness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remains', '[rɪ\'meɪnz]', 'n.剩余物；遗迹；遗体', '1. After maintenance the main remains and remainders are left on the domain. 维修之后，主要遗骸和剩余物留在了领地上。 2. After the wheat crop has been gathered, many farmers burn the remains and plough the ash into the soil, so as to enrich it. 小麦收割完成后，农夫们把剩余物烧掉，然后用犁把灰埋入地里，使土地更肥沃。 3. Not a vestige of the abbey remains. 那修道院的遗迹已荡然无存。 4. They have found prehistoric remains. 他们发现了史前遗迹。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('repeat', '[rɪ\'piːt]', 'n.重复；反复 v.重复；复述 adj.重复的；反复的', '1. A repeat of a television program is boring. 电视节目的重播是很乏味的。 2. Malcolm is forced to repeat crimes on himself. 马尔康不得不反复声言自己有罪。 3. Repeat this process repetitively, each time going farther and farther from the dog. 反复这一过程，逐渐地加大你与狗之间的距离。 4. The teacher asked him to repeat what he had said. 老师要他重复他所讲的话。 5. You can also specify the repeat interval for the probe. 你还可以指定探测器的重复间隔。', '形容词: repeatable 名词: repeatability 过去式: repeated 过去分词: repeated 现在分词: repeating 第三人称单数: repeats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('worse', '[wɜːrs]', 'adj.更坏的；更差的；更严重的 adv.更坏；更差 n.更坏的事物', '1. The weather is getting worse and worse. 天气越来越坏。 2. As time goes by my memory seems to get worse . 随着时间的流逝，我的记忆力越来越差。 3. It\'s even worse if you have a balcony. 如果你有阳台的话情况会更糟。 4. I\'m afraid he is getting steadily worse. 恐怕他的病情越来越严重了。 5. He is behaving worse than ever. 他的所作所为比以前更坏。 6. We thought that the situation was as bad as it could be, but worse was to follow. 我们还以为那是最坏的情况呢，可没想到更糟的还在后面。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pulse', '[pʌls]', 'n.脉搏；脉冲；[植]豆类 v.搏动；跳动', '1. His pulse is not very regular. 他的脉搏不很规则。 2. The excitement quickened my pulse. 激动使我的心跳加快。 3. I could feel a fluttering pulse. 我感到脉搏跳动。 4. The machine emits sound pulses. 这台机器可发出声脉冲信号。 5. I could feel blood pulsing through my veins. 我感到浑身血液在沸腾。', '过去式: pulsed 过去分词: pulsed 现在分词: pulsing 第三人称单数: pulses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('subject', '[\'sʌbdʒɪkt]', 'n.话题；科目；主题；题材；主观；[语]主语 n.实验对象；(君主国)国民 adj.易患的；服从的 vt.使服从；使隶属；使遭遇', '1. She dare not mention the subject again. 她不敢重提那个话题。 2. Mathematics is her favorite subject. 数学是她喜欢的科目。 3. He is said to be writing a paper on this subject. 据说他正在写一篇关于这个主题的论文。 4. Hawthorne concedes that normal life can be a subject for art. 霍桑承认日常生活可以作为艺术的题材。 5. We need some male subjects for a psychology experiment. 我们需要几个男子作心理学实验对象。 6. Mary is very subject to colds. 玛丽很容易患感冒。 7. Ancient Rome subjected most of Europe 古罗马帝国征服了欧洲大部分。', '名词: subjection 过去式: subjected 过去分词: subjected 现在分词: subjecting 第三人称单数: subjects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plantation', '[plæn\'teɪʃn]', 'n.种植园；造林地；殖民地', '1. There were hundreds of slaves in the plantation. 这个种植园里有数百名奴隶。 2. The flood destroyed the corn plantation. 洪水毁掉了玉米种植园。 3. According to initial plan,a total of 34 million hectares of plantation will be built. 初步规划，这些治理区的总造林是3400万公顷。 4. Demands for slaves now depend on the amount of plantation types in the game. 对奴隶的需求现在取决于游戏中殖民地类型的数量。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('generator', '[\'dʒenəreɪtər]', 'n.发电机；发生器', '1. The propeller turns a small D.C. generator. 螺旋桨带动一个小型直流发电机。 2. If you have, then The Idea Generator is for you. 如果你有，那么发电机理念是为你。 3. Let\'s purify air with a negative ion generator. 我们用负离子发生器净化一下空气吧。 4. Well, it\'s essentially a random number generator. 好，基本上就是一个随机数发生器。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('indeed', '[ɪn\'diːd]', 'adv.真正地；的确，确实；事实上；甚至', '1. I was very glad indeed to hear the news. 我听到这消息的确非常高兴。 2. He is a great man indeed. 他实在是一个伟人。 3. Indeed he has a solemn face, but he is very humorous at heart. 他的确有一副严肃的脸孔，但内心却是很富幽默感。 4. I don\'t mind. Indeed, I am delighted to help. 我不在乎。其实,我很乐意帮忙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('politics', '[\'pɑːlətɪks]', 'n.政治；政治学；政治活动；政治策略；政见', '1. This letter does not pertain to politics. 这封信的内容与政治无关。 2. He is not interested in politics. 他不喜欢政治。 3. In politics Britain has preferred evolution to revolution. 在政治上，英国喜欢渐进而不喜欢革命。 4. He has serious aspirations to a career in politics. 他有从政的雄心壮志。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peer', '[pɪr]', 'n.同辈；同等的人；贵族 vi.凝视；窥视', '1. Children are easily influenced by their peers. 孩子很容易受同辈影响。 2. He was valued by both his peer and his superiors. 他的同级和上级都很器重他。 3. The opinions of his peers are more important to him than his parents\' ideas. 在他看来，他同辈人的观点比他父母的观点更为重要。 4. It will not be easy to find his peer. 很不容易找到像他那样的人. 5. She peers through the mist, trying to find the right path. 她透过雾眯着眼看，想找出正确的路。', '过去式: peered 过去分词: peered 现在分词: peering 第三人称单数: peers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('burglar', '[\'bɜːrɡlər]', 'n.窃贼', '1. The governor pardoned the burglar. 州长赦免了那个窃贼。 2. Did a burglar break into your house last night? 昨晚有个窃贼闯进你家吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stake', '[steɪk]', 'n.桩；赌注；利害关系 v.用桩支撑；下注', '1. He drove a stake into the ground. 他向地里打了一根桩子。 2. This decision puts our lives at stake. 这么一决定,我们的生命就吉凶难卜了。 3. Most parents feel that they have a stake in their children\'s future,and so will use every effort to help them. 大多数家长认为，孩子们的前途和他们有利害关系，所以尽一切努力帮助他们。 4. He put up a stake to support the newly planted tree. 他竖了一根桩支撑新种的树。', '过去式: staked 过去分词: staked 现在分词: staking 第三人称单数: stakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('profession', '[prə\'feʃn]', 'n.职业；声明；行业；信仰', '1. He is a doctor by profession. 他的职业是医生。 2. Nursing is a vocation as well as a profession. 护理工作既是职业又是救死扶伤的责任。 3. I don\'t believe her profession of friendship for us. 我不相信她声称同我们友好。 4. He is a leading member of the medical profession. 他是医疗业中首屈一指的医生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kindness', '[\'kaɪndnəs]', 'n.仁慈；好意；友好的行为', '1. Her motherly kindness attaches us all to her. 她像母亲一般仁慈，我们大家都很依恋她。 2. Love is patience, and contains kindness. 爱情是耐性,而且包含仁慈。 3. Your kindness quite overwhelmed me. 你的好意使我感激难言。 4. Kindness always begets kindness. 善有善果。', '形容词: kind 副词: kindly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transition', '[træn\'zɪʃn]', 'n.转变；过渡', '1. Such a sudden transition must affect her. 这样的一个突然变化一定会影响她。 2. His attitude underwent an abrupt transition. 他的态度突然改变了。 3. We hope there will be a peaceful transition to the new system. 我们希望能够和平过渡到新的制度。', '形容词: transitional 副词: transitionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nasty', '[\'næsti]', 'adj.下流的；严重的；令人不快的；难懂的；危害的', '1. He is a person with a nasty mind. 他是个思想肮脏的人。 2. It\'s a tacky,nasty little movie,frankly. 坦率地说,那是一部低级下流、微不足道的影片。 3. The dog gave me a nasty nip on the leg. 那狗在我腿上狠咬了一口。 4. I was frightened when I saw the nasty gash in her arm. 她胳膊上又深又长的大伤口吓坏了我。', '副词: nastily 比较级: nastier 最高级: nastiest 名词: nastiness 名词复数: nasties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('announce', '[ə\'naʊns]', 'vt.宣布；宣告；预示；播报 vi.作播音员；宣布竞选', '1. I hope to announce the winner shortly. 我希望马上宣布胜利者的名字。 2. The president will announce a momentous decision. 主席将宣布重要决定。 3. We can go out to people and announce Good News. 我们能够走向人们，宣告天国的好消息。 4. I will always announce my goals to the world. 我要常常向世人宣告我的目标。 5. Cindy announces four programs a week. 辛迪一星期担任四个节目的播音员。', '过去式: announced 过去分词: announced 现在分词: announcing 第三人称单数: announces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conversation', '[ˌkɑːnvər\'seɪʃn]', 'n.谈话；会话', '1. I listened to their conversation. 我倾听他们的谈话。 2. Did you have a conversation with him? 你和他谈过话了吗？ 3. The band drowned our conversation. 乐队的演奏声把我们谈话的声音淹没了。 4. His French has come on a lot since he joined the conversation class. 他自从参加了会话班，法语取得了很大进步。', '形容词: conversational 副词: conversationally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mail', '[meɪl]', 'n.邮件；邮政 vt.邮寄', '1. I opened my mail and was surprised to see a broken vase. 我打开了邮件，惊讶地发现了一个打碎的花瓶。 2. Is there another mail in the afternoon? 下午还另有一批邮件吗？ 3. Some mail came for you this morning. 今天上午有你的邮件。 4. Our products are available by mail order. 我们的产品可用邮政划拨。 5. I went to the post office to mail the letters. 我去邮局寄信。', '形容词: mailable 名词: mailability 过去式: mailed 过去分词: mailed 现在分词: mailing 第三人称单数: mails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mistress', '[\'mɪstrəs]', 'n.主妇；女主人；情妇', '1. Wealth is a good servant, a very bad mistress. 财富是个好仆人，也是一个坏主妇。 2. Experience is the mistress of fools. 经验是蠢货的主妇。 3. The dog ran alongside his mistress. 狗在女主人的身边奔跑。 4. Rogue and mistress of Patterne do not go together. 罗格与帕忒恩的女主人不能并列。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overtime', '[\'oʊvərtaɪm]', 'n.加班时间(加班加点费)；(比赛)延长时间 adv.在规定时间之外(超出时间地)', '1. We did a deal with the management on overtime. 在加班问题上我们与管理部门达成一项协议。 2. We\'re in dispute (with the management) about overtime rates. 我们正(与资方)交涉加班费问题。 3. This game is going to go into overtime. 这场比赛将进行加时赛。 4. I got one point in the last minute of overtime. 在延长赛的最后一分钟我得了一分。 5. This new order will mean working overtime. 这一新定单意味着得加班加点.', '过去式: overtimed 过去分词: overtimed 现在分词: overtiming 第三人称单数: overtimes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('colonel', '[\'kɜːrnl]', 'n.上校', '1. A colonel is subordinate to a brigadier general. 上校级别低于准将。 2. The colonel paraded his soldiers. 上校集合士兵列队接受检阅。', '名词: colonelcy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('southeast', '[ˌsaʊθ\'iːst]', 'n.东南；东南地区 adj.东南的；向东南的；来自东南的 adv.往东南；来自东南；在东南', '1. Taiwan is in the southeast of China. 台湾在中国的东南部。 2. The wind is in the southeast. 东南部有风。 3. Kowloon is a city of southeast China. 九龙是中国东南一城市。 4. The inneer terrain tilted from the northwest to southeast. 境内地势由西北向东南倾斜。 5. From Jinggangshan we drove southeast to Ruijin. 从井岗山，我们往东南直取瑞金。', '形容词: southeastern');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refreshment', '[rɪ\'freʃmənt]', 'n.恢复；精神爽快；提神之事物 （复数）refreshments:点心； 茶点.', '1. Refreshment was served after the benediction. 牧师祝福后，有茶点招待弟兄姐妹。 2. So they went to a refreshment room. 于是他们来到茶点室。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('on', '[ɑːn]', 'prep.在 ... 之上；由 ... 支撑着；在（某一天）；关于；基于 adv.穿着；向前（移动)；表示持续性 adj.表示已连接、处于工作状态或使用中；发生；值班', '1. The book is on the table. 书在桌子上。 2. The spider is walking on the ceiling. 蜘蛛在天花板上爬行。 3. I bought it on credit. 这东西我是赊购来的。 4. He studied at Oxford on a Rhodes scholarship. 他靠罗兹奖学金在牛津就读。 5. Put your coat on. 穿上你的大衣. 6. The televisionw set was on. 电视机开着。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('congratulate', '[kən\'grætʃəˌleɪt]', 'vt.祝贺；庆祝', '1. Let me congratulate you. 请允许我向您表示祝贺。 2. May I congratulate you? 请允许我向您表示祝贺。 3. I congratulate you on your great discovery. 我祝贺你的伟大发现。 4. I congratulated myself on my narrow escape. 我庆祝自己死里逃生。', '形容词: congratulatory 名词: congratulator 过去式: congratulated 过去分词: congratulated 现在分词: congratulating 第三人称单数: congratulates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recur', '[rɪ\'kɜːr]', 'vi.重现；再发生', '1. What do you want to make it recur? 如果你能选择的话，你希望让什么重现？ 2. The best way to ensure quality is to write tests that validate data and algorithms and verify that prior mistakes do not recur. 确保质量的最佳方法是编写验证数据和算法并确认以前的错误不再重现的测试。 3. Our patient was successfully treated with diuretics, and the chylothorax did not recur during the following 12 months under a sodium-restricted diet. 此病患成功地以利尿剂治疗且合并低钠饮食的控制下，经一年的追踪，乳糜胸并未再发生。', '名词: recurrence 过去式: recurred 过去分词: recurred 现在分词: recurring 第三人称单数: recurs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('journalist', '[\'dʒɜːrnəlɪst]', 'n.记者；新闻工作者', '1. This journalist\'s works are popular among young people. 这位新闻记者的著作很受年轻人的欢迎。 2. The journalist was probing into several financial scandals. 那记者正在调查几起财务丑闻。 3. He is not so much a journalist as a writer. 与其说他是个新闻工作者, 不如说他是个作家。 4. His passport says he is a journalist. 他的护照说他是一个新闻工作者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('secretary', '[\'sekrəteri]', 'n.部长；秘书；书记；大臣；写字台', '1. He was the then secretary of Defense. 他是当时的国防部长。 2. He buzzed for his secretary to come. 他按蜂鸣器叫秘书进来。 3. My secretary is an absolute gem. 我的秘书真是个难能可贵的人。 4. At this moment she noticed the secretary coming in. 这时她注意到书记走了进来。', '形容词: secretarial 名词复数: secretaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cape', '[keɪp]', 'n.岬；海角 n.披肩', '1. Rudolf was rounding a bleak, dangerous cape. 鲁道夫正在绕过一个荒凉险峻的海岬。 2. The cape extends far into the ocean. 那海岬伸向海洋远处。 3. My favorite movie is Cape No. 7. 我最喜欢的电影是”海角七号”。 4. The man has a red cape. 这人有一件红色的斗篷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('margin', '[\'mɑːrdʒən]', 'n.边缘；余地；幅度；利润；差额；页边空白；定金；【商】原价和卖价之差 vt.加边于；为…付保证金', '1. We came to the margin of the wood. 我们来到树林的边缘。 2. We allowed a margin of 20 minutes in catching the train. 我们有20分钟的余地赶火车。 3. There is no margin for error in our plan. 我们的计划中不留有误差幅度。 4. Our pricing policy aims at producing a 35% gross margin. 我们的定价政策目的在于赢得35%的毛利润。 5. The shore was margined with foam. 岸边都是泡沫。', '形容词: margined 过去式: margined 过去分词: margined 现在分词: margining 第三人称单数: margins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('function', '[\'fʌŋkʃn]', 'n.职务；功能；函数；重大聚会；应变量，有相关关系者；取决于 vi.运行；起作用', '1. What is his function on the committee? 他在委员会里担任什么职务? 2. The teacher did not explain its grammatical function. 老师没有解释它的文法功能。 3. The function of the ear is to listen. 耳的功能是听。 4. Periodic change imposed on a controlled variable or a function by a controller. 通过控制器控制某一变量或函数进行周期性变化。 5. However, many system features and tasks will not function correctly. 但是,许多系统功能和任务将无法正常运行。', '形容词: functionless 过去式: functioned 过去分词: functioned 现在分词: functioning 第三人称单数: functions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dozen', '[\'dʌzn]', 'n.(一)打；十二个 adj.一打的；十二个的', '1. How much are those apples a dozen? 那些苹果一打多少钱？ 2. He gave me a dozen of roses for my birthday. 他在我生日那天送我了一打玫瑰。 3. I had bred a dozen of chickens. 我饲养了12只小鸡。 4. There were about a dozen of them. 大约有十二人。 5. My mother bought a dozen eggs. 我妈妈买了一打鸡蛋。', '形容词: dozenth');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('widow', '[\'wɪdoʊ]', 'n.寡妇；遗孀 vt.使丧偶', '1. The widow lamented the death of her only child. 寡妇为她独生子的死而悲痛。 2. The poor widow earns money by taking in washing. 那位可怜的寡妇在家里替人洗衣服度日。 3. I should assist his widow and daughters. 我一定要帮助他的遗孀和女儿们。 4. All this money was appropriated for the support of his widow. 所有这些钱作为给他的遗孀的抚养费。', '过去式: widowed 过去分词: widowed 现在分词: widowing 第三人称单数: widows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('microscope', '[\'maɪkrəskoʊp]', 'n.显微镜', '1. He focuses the lens of a microscope. 他调整显微镜的透镜以定焦点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fond', '[fɑːnd]', 'adj.溺爱的；喜欢的；愚蠢的；渴望的', '1. A fond mother may spoil her child. 溺爱的母亲可能会宠坏她的孩子。 2. The fond father smiled with pleasure. 溺爱孩子的父亲高兴地微笑了。 3. I am not fond of solitude. 我不喜欢孤独。 4. He was fond of drawing when he was a child. 他还是个孩子时就喜欢画画。', '副词: fondly 比较级: fonder 最高级: fondest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pocket', '[\'pɑːkɪt]', 'n.口袋；袋子；球袋；钱；小块地方；在...掌握之中；保障金 adj.小型的；孤立的；局部的 v.装…在口袋里；私吞；击(球)落袋', '1. He took a book out of his pocket. 他从口袋里拿出一本书。 2. You will find information about safety procedures in the pocket in front of you. 在您座位前方的袋子里有安全措施须知。 3. Hit the ball into one of the side pockets. 把球打进其中一个侧边袋。 4. The gem is beyond my pocket. 这颗宝石我可买不起。 5. He always carries a pocket dictionary with him. 他总是随身携带一本袖珍字典。 6. He pocketed his wallet and car keys. 他把钱包和汽车钥匙放进了衣袋里。', '形容词: pocketable 过去式: pocketed 过去分词: pocketed 现在分词: pocketing 第三人称单数: pockets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('significance', '[sɪɡ\'nɪfɪkəns]', 'n.重要性；意义', '1. Few people realized the significance of the discovery. 很少有人意识到这一发现的重要性. 2. They failed to appreciate significance of the precautions. 他们没有意识到这些预防措施的重要性。 3. Our boss urged on us the significance of punctuality. 老板向我们强调守时的重要性。 4. He puzzled out the significance of the statement. 他解释了这一论断的意义。', '异体字: significancy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('garment', '[\'ɡɑːrmənt]', 'n.衣服 vt.给 ... 披上衣服；覆上 ...', '1. This garment should be washed carefully. 这件衣服应该小心地洗涤。 2. The garment fits her perfectly. 这件衣服她穿上很合适。 3. In spring nature wears a new garment. 春天', '过去式: garmented 过去分词: garmented 现在分词: garmenting 第三人称单数: garments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tribute', '[\'trɪbjuːt]', 'n.贡品；称赞；敬意；礼物', '1. The victorious nations are demanding tribute from their former enemies. 战胜国要求战败国向其进奉贡品。 2. Many Greek cities had to send yearly tribute to Athens. 许多希腊城市不得不每年向雅典进贡。 3. The musician gave full tribute to his former teacher. 这位音乐家盛赞了他过去的老师。 4. He paid tribute to the way the country had forged national unity. 他称赞这个国家加强民族团结的方式。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enrich', '[ɪn\'rɪtʃ]', 'vt.使富足；使肥沃；使丰富', '1. The expanding economy enriched the peasants. 不断发展的经济使农民们富裕起来。 2. The library was enriched with new books. 购买新书使图书馆得到了充实。 3. Farmers enrich the soil with organic and inorganic manures. 农民用有机肥料和无机肥料来提高土壤的肥力。 4. An appreciation of art will enrich your life. 艺术欣赏将会丰富你的生活', '名词: enricher 过去式: enriched 过去分词: enriched 现在分词: enriching 第三人称单数: enriches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gap', '[ɡæp]', 'n.缺口；裂缝；差距；空白', '1. He has a gap between his two front teeth. 他的两个门牙之间有一缺口。 2. A big gap yawned between the rocks. 岩石间豁开一个大裂口。 3. They planed to narrow the gap between imports and exports. 他们计划缩小进出口的差额。 4. Reducing the gap between rich and poor is one of the main challenges facing the government. 缩小贫富之间的差距是政府面临的主要难题之一。', '过去式: gapped 过去分词: gapped 现在分词: gapping 第三人称单数: gaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chip', '[tʃɪp]', 'n.缺口；碎屑；油炸土豆条；薄片；筹码；芯片；（足球）高球；（高尔夫球）近穴球 v.形成（缺口）；切下；凿下；凑份子；打高球；近穴击球；将（土豆等）切条', '1. It was difficult finding two cups without some kind of chip on them. 很难找到两个一点没有缺口的杯子。 2. A small chip of ice flew into the air. 一小块碎冰飞溅到了空中。 3. She had a hamburger and a portion of chip. 她吃了一个汉堡包和一份炸薯条。 4. I\'ve got chocolate chip for you. 我给你们买了巧克力薄片。 5. Be careful with these plates they chip very easily. 小心这些盘子--边缘容易破损。', '过去式: chipped 过去分词: chipped 现在分词: chipping 第三人称单数: chips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sing', '[sɪŋ]', 'v.唱；鸣叫；歌颂；称赞；<俚>告密 n.合唱会 abbr.单数的（=singular）', '1. She was singing a lullaby to her child. 她正在给孩子唱摇篮曲。 2. Let\'s sing a song during the break. 我们趁这空当儿唱支歌。 3. She sang the baby to sleep. 她给孩子唱歌唱到孩子睡着。 4. Birds sing loudest in the early morning. 鸟儿在清晨高声歌唱。 5. Did you join in the community sing? 你们有没有参加社区的合唱会?', '形容词: singable 过去式: sang/sung 过去分词: sung 现在分词: singing 第三人称单数: sings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('curse', '[kɜːrs]', 'n.诅咒；咒骂；祸端 vt.诅咒；咒骂；使受罪 vi.诅咒；咒骂', '1. Our tribe is under a curse. 我们的部落正受诅咒。 2. He muttered a curse at the other driver. 他低声咒骂另一位开车的人。 3. Foxes can be a curse to farmers. 狐狸可给农民带来祸害。 4. She cursed him for ruining her life. 她诅咒他，说他毁了她的一生。 5. The Fore knew kuru as a curse cast by sorcerers. 弗尔族人认为，库鲁是由男巫发出的诅咒。', '名词: curser 过去式: cursed/curst 过去分词: cursed/curst 现在分词: cursing 第三人称单数: curses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('insist', '[ɪn\'sɪst]', 'vt.坚持；坚决主张 vi.坚持；强调', '1. He insisted that he had done right. 他坚决认为自己做对了。 2. They insist that I stay there for supper. 他们坚决要求让我留下吃晚饭。 3. Since you insist, I must amend the letter of credit. 既然你坚持，我就只好修改信用证。 4. He insisted on paying for the meal. 他坚持要付饭钱。', '副词: insistingly 名词: insistence 过去式: insisted 过去分词: insisted 现在分词: insisting 第三人称单数: insists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('solve', '[sɑːlv]', 'v.解决；解答', '1. This problem is too difficult for me to solve. 这个问题太难,我解决不了。 2. It is so clever of you to have solved the puzzle. 你能解答那个难题真是聪明。', '名词: solver 过去式: solved 过去分词: solved 现在分词: solving 第三人称单数: solves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ally', '[\'ælaɪ]', 'n.同盟国；同盟者；伙伴 v.（使）结盟；（使）联合', '1. The ally of the working class was the peasantry. 工人阶级的同盟军是农民阶级。 2. Britain was an ally of America in the World War I. 英国在第一次世界大战中是美国的同盟国。 3. That football team is our ally. 那个足球队是我们的同盟者。 4. Japan is a leading trading partner and security ally of the United States. 日本是美国的主要贸易伙伴和安全盟国。 5. We will ally our forces with the army from the north. 我们将与北方的部队结盟。', '名词复数: allies 过去式: allied 过去分词: allied 现在分词: allying 第三人称单数: allies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('episode', '[\'epɪsoʊd]', 'n.一段情节；片段；轶事；插曲', '1. The first episode goes out next Friday evening at 8.00 pm. 下星期五晚上8时播出第一集。 2. Relating to or resembling an episode. 插曲似的关于或类似插曲的 3. One of the funniest episodes in the book occurs in chapter 6. 书中最有趣的情节是在第6章。 4. The episode of this film sounds good. 这部电影的插曲很好听。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('incorporate', '[ɪn\'kɔːrpəreɪt]', 'v.合并；组成公司 adj.合并的；公司组织的', '1. I will incorporate the new findings in my report. 我要把新发现并入我的报告。 2. This company is about to incorporate with its parent company. 这公司将要与其母公司合并。 3. We had to incorporate for a company for tax reasons. 鉴于税务原因，我们得组成公司。', '形容词: incorporable 名词: incorporation 过去式: incorporated 过去分词: incorporated 现在分词: incorporating 第三人称单数: incorporates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wound', '[wuːnd]', 'n.创伤；伤害；伤口 v.伤；伤害；缠绕（动词wind的过去式和过去分词）', '1. I hope her emotional wound will heal with the passing of time. 我希望她感情上的创伤能随时间的流逝而治愈。 2. She got deep psychological wounds. 她受到很深的心理创伤。 3. The soldier received a serious wound on the chest. 这名士兵胸部受了重伤。 4. That was a wound to the child\'s pride. 那是对孩子自尊心的伤害。 5. Two soldiers died and three others were wounded in the attack. 在这次袭击中,有两名士兵牺牲,三名受伤。', '副词: woundedly 过去式: wounded 过去分词: wounded 现在分词: wounding 第三人称单数: wounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diminish', '[dɪ\'mɪnɪʃ]', 'vt.减少；减损；贬低 vi.变少；逐渐变细', '1. We should try to diminish the cost of production. 我们应尽力减少生产成本。 2. His illness diminished his health. 疾病侵蚀了他的健康。 3. He likes to diminish the skills of others. 他喜欢贬低别人的技能。 4. The amount of water in the pond will diminish as the dry season continues. 如果旱季还持续下去，池塘中的水量将减少。', '形容词: diminishable 名词: diminishment 过去式: diminished 过去分词: diminished 现在分词: diminishing 第三人称单数: diminishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('formula', '[\'fɔːrmjələ]', 'n.配方；公式；规则；代乳品 adj.方程式的；（赛车的）级的', '1. They are working on the perfection of their new paint formula. 他们正在努力研制尽善尽美的新颜料配方。 2. What is the formula for water? 水的分子式是什么？ 3. Within the braces, you can include any formula. 在大括号内,可以包含任何公式。 4. It\'s the formula for converting gallons into liters. 这是加仑与升的换算公式。 5. His outwardly relaxed manner hides a sharp mind and a keen will to win, something he did a lot of on the nursery slopes of Formula BMW. 他轻松自若的举止下隐藏着敏锐的心思和渴望胜利的决心，这在他参加宝马方程式的培养期里就已经有所体现。', '形容词: formulaic 副词: formulaically 名词复数: formulas');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('especially', '[ɪ\'speʃəli]', 'adv.特别；尤其', '1. Their main exports are textiles, especially silk and cotton. 他们的主要出口货物是纺织品，特别是丝绸和棉布。 2. The rising sun is especially beautiful to look at from this angle. 旭日从这个角度看起来特别美。 3. I love the country, especially in spring. 我喜欢这乡村，尤其是在春天。 4. Christmas is a time of mirth, especially for children. 圣诞节是个快乐的日子，尤其是对孩子们。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blaze', '[bleɪz]', 'n.火焰；烈火；光辉；(光或色彩的)展现；(感情的)迸发；(动物面部的)白斑；记号 v.燃烧；发光；迸发；传播；在(树皮)上刻记号', '1. We warmed our hands near the blaze of the campfire. 我们在篝火的火焰旁暖手。 2. The firemen were unable to control the blaze. 消防队员无法控制这场大火。 3. Seven people died in the blaze at the nightclub. 在夜总会的熊熊烈火中有七人丧生。 4. The blaze of your eyes can burn the beaven and earth. 双瞳的光辉足以灼烧大地。 5. The following morning the building was still blazing. 第二天早上,大楼还在燃烧。', '副词: blazingly 过去式: blazed 过去分词: blazed 现在分词: blazing 第三人称单数: blazes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('greenhouse', '[\'ɡriːnhaʊs]', 'n.温室；暖房', '1. They had to smoke the plants in a greenhouse. 他们只好用烟熏温室里的植物。 2. Most vegetables we buy in winter are nurtured in the greenhouse. 我们冬天买的大多数蔬菜都是在温室里培育的。 3. Carbon dioxide is the largest contributor to the greenhouse effect. 二氧化碳太多是道致温室效应的最主要原因。 4. Behind the house is a greenhouse. 在那所房子後面是一个暖房。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relevant', '[\'reləvənt]', 'adj.相关的；切题的；中肯的；有重大关系的；有意义的，目的明确的', '1. A paper relevant to this research was published by him. 与本研究相关的一篇论文是他发表的。 2. Have you heard of the relevant report? 你听说过相关的报道吗? 3. My next conclusion is more relevant. 我的另一个结论更切题。 4. Portraits of people will draw readers\'attention, especially if the images are relevant and tell a story. 人物肖像可以吸引读者的注意,当图像切题并在讲述一个故事时更是如此。', '副词: relevantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('get', '[ɡet]', 'v.得到；使得；抓住；克服；明白；激怒；患（病）；达到 n.生育；后代；救球', '1. The problem is when to get the money we need. 问题是什么时候能得到我们所需要的钱。 2. If Peter had applied for the post, he would probably get it now. 要是彼得申请了那职位,他很可能现在就得到了。 3. She soon got the children ready for school. 她很快帮孩子做好上学的准备。 4. Do you think you\'ll get the work finished on time? 你认为你的工作可以如期完成吗？', '形容词: getable 过去式: got 过去分词: gotten/got 现在分词: getting 第三人称单数: gets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('triple', '[\'trɪpl]', 'adj.有三部分的；三倍的 v.（使）成三倍 n.三个一组；三倍之数；（垒）三垒打', '1. The plan has a triple purpose. 该计划有三个目的。 2. I want a triple room with mountain view. 我想要一间向山的三人房。 3. Its population is about triple that of Venice. 它的人口大约是威尼斯的三倍。 4. The price is triple of what it\'s actually worth. 这个价格是它实际价值的三倍。 5. Output should triple by next year. 到明年产量应增至三倍。 6. Twelve is the triple of four. 十二是四的三倍数。', '过去式: tripled 过去分词: tripled 现在分词: tripling 第三人称单数: triples');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('schedule', '[\'skedʒuːl]', 'n.时间表，日程；一览表；计划 v.预定；安排；编制目录', '1. I\'ll work out the schedule. 我来拟定时间表。 2. Please show me the taxation schedule. 请让我看看税收一览表。 3. Owing to various delays en route, we arrived two days behind schedule. 由于路上的种种耽搁, 我们比原计划迟到了两天。 4. He was scheduled to attend the party. 他预定出席那个宴会。', '形容词: schedular 名词: scheduler 过去式: scheduled 过去分词: scheduled 现在分词: scheduling 第三人称单数: schedules');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('divine', '[dɪ\'vaɪn]', 'adj.神圣的；神的 vt.推断 vi.预言；理解 n.牧师；神学家', '1. In the Dragon Pond are divine fish. 可都是龙潭里的神鱼啊。 2. Her elegance and beauty was simply divine. 她高雅的气质和美丽的外表简直是上天的恩赐。 3. That play we saw last night was simply divine! 我们昨天晚上看的那出戏真是好极了！ 4. To err is human,to forgive is divine. 犯错误是人之常情，宽恕才难能可贵。 5. At last I divined the truth. 我终于看穿了事情的真相。 6. I don\'t believe that astrologers are able to divine. 我不相信占星家能作预言。 7. He was selected to be a divine for the church. 他被选为教堂的牧师。', '副词: divinely 比较级: diviner 最高级: divinest 名词: divineness 过去式: divined 过去分词: divined 现在分词: divining 第三人称单数: divines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lose', '[luːz]', 'vt.丢失；失败；削减；丧生；看不到；亏损；迷失 vi.失败；经受损失；走慢', '1. I lost my wallet yesterday. 我昨天丢了钱包。 2. It\'s only the second time the team has lost a match this season. 那仅仅是本赛季该队的第二次失利而已。 3. The game will lose its relish when you grow old. 你年纪大了以后,就会发现这种游戏的趣味大打折扣了。 4. He lost his life in the war. 他在战争中丧生。 5. Merely to maintain is to lose in the end. 止步不前,终将遭到失败。', '过去式: lost 过去分词: lost 现在分词: losing 第三人称单数: loses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('herd', '[hɜːrd]', 'n.兽群；牧人；群 vt.放牧；群集；使 ... 成群，把…赶到一起 vi.聚在一起', '1. A large herd could wreck a train. 庞大的兽群将会使火车失事。 2. The report of the gun will scare the herd. 枪声会惊吓兽群。 3. The herdsman looks after a herd of animals. 牧人放牧着一群牲畜。 4. The Goatherd scolded them for their ingratitude in leaving him, when during the storm he had taken more care of them than of his own herd. 牧人骂他们忘恩负义说他曾经在风雪中对他们照顾得比自己的羊还好。 5. Dogs are often trained to herd sheep. 狗常被训练来放羊。 6. You should not herd with the man as him. 你不应和他那样的人来往。', '过去式: herded 过去分词: herded 现在分词: herding 第三人称单数: herds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('orange', '[\'ɔːrɪndʒ]', 'n.橙子，橘子；橙黄色 adj.橙色的', '1. Would you peel me an orange? 你给我剥一个橘子好吗？ 2. Which one do you prefer, an apple or an orange? 你想要哪个，苹果还是橘子？ 3. There are some oranges on the table. 桌子上有几个橘子。 4. The burning coals started to flame yellow and orange. 燃烧著的煤开始发出了黄色与橙色的火焰。 5. The sun looked like an orange globe. 太阳看上去象只橘黄色的球体。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('awkward', '[\'ɔːkwərd]', 'adj.尴尬的；笨拙的；（设计）别扭的', '1. It\'s a little awkward, because he\'s my friend but I\'m still his boss. 他是我朋友,而我又是他老板,这真有点尴尬。 2. He felt awkward and uncomfortable. 他感到尴尬和不舒服。 3. He seemed as awkward and rough as ever. 他跟从前一样拙笨和粗鲁。 4. Swans are surprisingly awkward on the land. 天鹅在陆地上笨的出奇。', '副词: awkwardly 名词: awkwardness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fairy', '[\'feri]', 'n.仙女；小精灵 adj.优雅的；幻想中的；虚构的', '1. The fairy godmother waved her (magic) wand. 助人仙女挥动她的魔杖。 2. There are many stories about the nymphs in Roman fairy tales. 罗马神话中有许多关于女神的故事。 3. The bad fairy laughed loudly again and left. 这个坏仙女再次狂笑然后离开。 4. I saw a fairy flying around in my dreams. 在梦里，我看见一个小精灵飞来飞去。 5. She is really a fairy girl. 她真是一个优雅灵巧的女孩。', '名词复数: fairies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shave', '[ʃeɪv]', 'v.刮；剃；修剪；掠过；<口>削减 n.剃须；修面；剃刀', '1. I lathered my face and started to shave. 我往脸上涂了皂沫，然后开始刮胡子。 2. He shaved his head bald. 他剃了个光头。 3. He asked me to shave the lawn. 他叫我修剪草坪。 4. The ball narrowly shaved his off stump. 那个球紧贴着他的三柱门的外柱掠过。 5. He had a shave and a bath. 他刮了脸，又洗了澡。', '过去式: shaved 过去分词: shaved/shaven 现在分词: shaving 第三人称单数: shaves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preclude', '[prɪ\'kluːd]', 'vt.阻止；排除', '1. That will preclude him from escaping. 那将阻止他逃走，那将使他无法逃走。 2. Their move does not preclude others from investing. 他们这一行动并不影响其他人进行投资。 3. My present finances preclude the possibility of buying a car. 按我目前的财务状况我是不可能买车的。 4. Small volume this year does not preclude huge volume next year. 今年业绩不多，不代表明年就一定会很少，', '形容词: preclusive 副词: preclusively 名词: preclusion 过去式: precluded 过去分词: precluded 现在分词: precluding 第三人称单数: precludes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('economics', '[ˌiːkə\'nɑːmɪks]', 'n.经济学', '1. She is studying economics at college. 她在大学里读经济学。 2. When they start talking about economics, I\'m out of my depth. 他们一谈起经济学，我就一窍不通了。 3. A knowledge of economics is fundamental to any understanding of this problem. 经济知识对于理解这个问题是至关重要的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('revive', '[rɪ\'vaɪv]', 'vt.使重生；恢复精神；唤醒 vi.复生', '1. We tried to revive him but without avail. 我们试图使他苏醒,但没有成功。 2. The flowers will revive in water. 这些花在水中会再活。 3. Revive your spirit and add shine to your hair. 重振你的精神，给你的头发增添光亮。 4. We need something to revive our hopes. 我们需要一些什么东西来重新恢复我们的希望。', '形容词: revivable 名词: reviver 过去式: revived 过去分词: revived 现在分词: reviving 第三人称单数: revives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contend', '[kən\'tend]', 'v.竞争；争斗；争辩；坚决主张', '1. Three armed groups were contending for power. 三个武装集团在争夺权力。 2. John has to contend with great difficulties. 约翰得与那些艰难困苦作斗争。 3. They have to contend against drought every year. 他们每年都得与干旱做斗争。 4. But the potential is simply too significant, the experts contend. 但是专家们主张，潜力是非常重要的。', '名词: contender 过去式: contended 过去分词: contended 现在分词: contending 第三人称单数: contends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inherent', '[ɪn\'hɪrənt]', 'adj.固有的；内在的', '1. Weight is an inherent property of matter. 重量是物质固有的特性。 2. The desire for freedom is inherent in us all. 渴望自由是我们大家生来就有的愿望。 3. She has an inherent love of beauty. 她天生爱美。 4. There is an inherent weakness in the design. 这设计本身存在弱点。', '副词: inherently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tan', '[tæn]', 'n.棕褐色；黝黑 v.晒黑；鞣(革)；<俚>痛打 adj.棕褐色的', '1. I bought a pair of tan leather shoes the other day. 前几天我买了双棕褐色的皮鞋。 2. It took me all summer to get this tan. 我花了整个夏天才晒出这样的棕褐色。 3. My tan\'s beginning to fade. 我晒黑的肤色逐渐变浅了。 4. The skin of your cheeks will tan. 你双颊的皮肤将被晒得黝黑. 5. These shoes are tan, not dark brown. 这些鞋是棕黄色的，不是深褐色的。', '形容词: tannish 比较级: tanner 最高级: tannest 过去式: tanned 过去分词: tanned 现在分词: tanning 第三人称单数: tans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seam', '[siːm]', 'n.缝；接缝 vt.缝合；接合；使有纹 vi.有裂缝', '1. We can mend a seam but not a big hole. 我们可以缝好脱线处，但不是补大洞。 2. The seam of her skirt ripped. 她的裙子的接缝裂开了。 3. You should seam up the shirt without using sewing-machine. 你不要用机器去缝制这件衬衣。 4. She seamed two pieces of carpet together. 她将两块地毯缝在一起。 5. The fields dried and seamed in the heat. 农田在高温下干裂。', '名词: seamer 过去式: seamed 过去分词: seamed 现在分词: seaming 第三人称单数: seams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('collect', '[kə\'lekt]', 'v.收集；聚集；募捐；运走；使（自己）镇定', '1. He used to collect cards, but now he likes to collect stamps. 他以前收集卡片,现在却喜欢收集邮票。 2. A crowd soon collected at the scene of the accident. 群众迅速聚集在出事现场。 3. He\'s collecting (money) for famine relief. 他正在为赈济饥民募捐. 4. The dustmen collect the rubbish once a week. 垃圾工每周运走一次垃圾.', '过去式: collected 过去分词: collected 现在分词: collecting 第三人称单数: collects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feel', '[fiːl]', 'v.感觉；觉得；触摸；摸起来；认为；摸索 n.感觉；触觉', '1. Can you feel the tension in this room? 你能觉察出这房间里的紧张气氛吗？ 2. Take a deep breath, and you will feel relaxed. 深深地吸一口气,那样你会觉得轻松的。 3. She felt the child\'s forehead to see if he was feverish. 她摸孩子的前额去看他是不是发烧了。 4. The sheets feels smooth. 被单摸上去很光滑。 5. The room has a nice cosy feel. 这房间给人非常温暖舒适的感觉。', '过去式: felt 过去分词: felt 现在分词: feeling 第三人称单数: feels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('auxiliary', '[ɔːɡ\'zɪliəri]', 'n.助动词；辅助物；帮助者 adj.辅助的；附加的', '1. In Chinese, the classification of the auxiliary verb and the adverb always have dispute. 摘要汉语中助动词和副词的分类一直有争议。 2. We have an auxiliary generator in case of power cuts. 我们有一台万一断电时使用的备用发电机。 3. She is an auxiliary nurse. 她是一名助理护士。', '名词复数: auxiliaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dubious', '[\'duːbiəs]', 'adj.怀疑的；可疑的；不确定的', '1. I feel dubious about his honesty. 我对他的诚实表示怀疑。 2. I am dubious about accepting the offer of the job. 我犹豫不定是否接受提供给我的那份工作。 3. I remain dubious about her motives. 我对她的动机仍存疑念。 4. The testimony given by him is dubious. 他所作的证据是可疑的。', '副词: dubiously 名词: dubiousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('steel', '[stiːl]', 'n.钢铁；钢制品；钢铁般的性质 vt.使坚强；使 ... 硬如钢；使下定决心 adj.钢的；坚强的', '1. The doctor inserted a steel plate into his damaged leg. 医生在他受伤的腿中植入了一块钢板。 2. The output value of iron and steel makes up one quarter of the country\'s national income. 钢铁制品创造的产值占据了国民收入的四分之一。 3. He is a man of steel who has experienced a lot of wars. 他是一个经历过许多战争、有着钢铁般意志的男人。 4. You should steel yourself against failure . 面对失败,你应该坚强起来。 5. The profits of the steel industry have fallen due to the measures of trade protectionism taken by that country. 由于那国采取的贸易保护主义措施,钢铁业的利润有所下降。', '过去式: steeled 过去分词: steeled 现在分词: steeling 第三人称单数: steels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mention', '[\'menʃn]', 'vt.提到；说起 n.提及；说起', '1. Speaking of Macao, it is necessary to mention lotus flowers. 说到澳门,就不得不提到莲花了。 2. Paul is highly intelligent, not to mention good-looking and rich. 保罗学识渊博,更不用说他还英俊富有呢! 3. He made no mention of having met her. 他不提他曾经和她见面。 4. She blushed at the mention of her love\'s name . 她因说到她情人的名字而脸红。', '形容词: mentionable 过去式: mentioned 过去分词: mentioned 现在分词: mentioning 第三人称单数: mentions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('amid', '[ə\'mɪd]', 'prep.在其间；在其中', '1. He sat down amid deafening applause. 他在震耳欲聋的掌声中就坐。 2. I stood amid a sea of corn. 我站在茫茫一片庄稼之中。 3. He is amid his enemies. 他被敌人包围。 4. We groped amid the darkness. 我们在黑暗中摸索。', '异体字: amidst');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pyramid', '[\'pɪrəmɪd]', 'n.金字塔；棱锥体；[证券]金字塔式交易法 v.急速增加；以金字塔的模型构建', '1. Egypt is famous for its grand pyramid. 埃及以巨大的金字塔闻名。 2. Lagrange is the lofty pyramid of mathematical sciences. 拉格朗日是数学科学中高耸的金字塔。 3. A pyramid provides a useful conceptual model for organizing scientific knowledge. 金字塔给科学知识的组织提供了一个有用的概念性模型。', '形容词: pyramidal 副词: pyramidally 过去式: pyramided 过去分词: pyramided 现在分词: pyramiding 第三人称单数: pyramids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abuse', '[ə\'bjuːs]', 'n.滥用；恶习 vt.滥用；辱骂；虐待', '1. The government has set up a working party to look into the problem of drug abuse. 政府已成立工作组调查滥用毒品问题。 2. His political reputation was tainted by his abuse of the power. 他因滥用职权而破坏了政治声誉。 3. He greeted me with a stream of abuse. 他见到我就连声辱骂。 4. It\'s easy to abuse one\'s power. 人容易滥用权力。', '名词: abuser 过去式: abused 过去分词: abused 现在分词: abusing 第三人称单数: abuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reliance', '[rɪ\'laɪəns]', 'n.信赖；所信赖的人或物', '1. I place complete reliance on his judgment. 我完全信赖他的判断。 2. I have no reliance about his assurance. 我不信赖他的保证。 3. Don\'t place too much reliance on what he said. 对他所说的话不要过于信赖。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ton', '[tʌn]', 'n.吨；<口>大量', '1. The maximum load for this lorry is one ton. 这辆卡车最大载重量是一吨。 2. How many tons does this elephant weigh? 这头大象重多少吨？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('merely', '[\'mɪrli]', 'adv.仅仅；只不过', '1. They are not merely content to fill the stomach. 他们不仅仅满足于填饱肚子。 2. I accepted this job merely for the high salary. 我仅仅是因为高薪才接受了这份工作。 3. She is merely a child. 她只不过是个孩子。 4. I merely suggest you should do it again. 我只是建议你重新做这件事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('luxury', '[\'lʌkʃəri]', 'n.奢侈品；奢侈；豪华', '1. The increasing sale of luxury goods is an index of the country\'s prosperity. 奢侈商品销售量日增是该国繁荣的标志。 2. The government has imposed strict controls over the import of luxury goods. 政府对奢侈品的进口采取了严格的管制。 3. If he can afford a luxury yacht, then a fortiori he can afford to pay his debts. 他若能买得起豪华的快艇，就更能匀出钱来还债了。 4. In old society, the gentry lived in luxury. 在旧社会，贵族们生活奢侈。', '名词复数: luxuries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('optical', '[\'ɑːptɪkl]', 'adj.视觉的；光学的', '1. The optical system of the eye stimulate cell of the retina. 眼睛的视觉系统刺激视网膜内的细胞。 2. A mirage is an optical illusion. 海市蜃楼是一种视错觉。 3. The canal on Mars is believed to be an optical illusion. 火星运河被认为是一种视觉错觉。 4. Microscopes and telescopes are optical instruments. 望远镜和显微镜是光学仪器。', '副词: optically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fragrant', '[\'freɪɡrənt]', 'adj.芬香的；馥郁的', '1. The aspic is one kind of strongly fragrant purple blue color floret. 薰衣草是一种馥郁的紫蓝色的小花。 2. Fragrant fruit juice is the best drink to entertain guests in the four seasons. 香气馥郁的果露饮料是四季酬宾美物。', '副词: fragrantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arbitrary', '[\'ɑːrbətreri]', 'adj.任意的；专制的；武断的；霸道的', '1. My choice was quite arbitrary. 我的选择相当随意。 2. I\'m not used to your arbitrary standards. 我不习惯你们那些随心所欲的标准。 3. Dictators are arbitrary rulers. 独裁者即独断专横的统治者。 4. This is an arbitrary decision. 这是个武断的决定。', '副词: arbitrarily 名词: arbitrariness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compatible', '[kəm\'pætəbl]', 'adj.一致的；兼容的；适合的 n.兼容', '1. The proposed new regulation is not compatible with the existing policy. 提出的新规定与现有的政策不符。 2. We should remain the compatible family relationships. 我们应该维持和谐的家庭关系。 3. He and his wife are not compatible 他跟他的妻子合不来。 4. It may not be compatible with your version of Mac OS X. 它可能与您的Mac OS X版本不兼容。 5. He drove a car at a speed compatible with safety. 他以安全速度行车。', '副词: compatibly 名词: compatibility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('with', '[wɪð]', 'prep.用；随着；包括；和 ... 一起', '1. They muffled up her head with a blanket. 他们用毯子蒙住了她的头。 2. The risk of severe illnesses increases with age. 患重病的风险随着年龄的增加而增加。 3. The week cost us over 500 but that was with skiing lessons. 这一周花了500多英镑，但其中包括滑雪课的学费。 4. I leave the baby with my mother every day. 我每天都把婴儿交给我母亲照料。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sway', '[sweɪ]', 'v.摇动；摇摆；支配；影响；说服，使相信 n.摇摆；支配；影响', '1. The branches of the trees were swaying in the wind. 树枝在风中摇晃。 2. Smokestacks are known to sway in the wind if they are not rigid enough. 如果烟囱没有足够的刚度；它就会在风中摇摆。 3. Do you sway your hips when you walk ? 你走路时摆动臀部吗? 4. His power sways the world. 他称霸天下。 5. sway of the ferry made him feel sick. 渡船摇摇晃晃,他感到恶心。', '副词: swayingly 名词: swayer 过去式: swayed 过去分词: swayed 现在分词: swaying 第三人称单数: sways');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dip', '[dɪp]', 'v.浸；蘸；下沉；倾斜；掏取；浏览 n.浸泡；浸；蘸；倾斜；下降', '1. The boat dipped into the waves. 小船沉没在波涛之中。 2. He dipped his pen in the ink. 他拿钢笔蘸墨水。 3. The children like to dip their bread into the milk. 孩子们喜欢把面包蘸牛奶吃。 4. The sun dipped below the horizon. 太阳落到地平线下。 5. On a hot day a dip in the sea is sheer paradise. 热天洗个海水澡是十分令人惬意的事。', '过去式: dipped 过去分词: dipped 现在分词: dipping 第三人称单数: dips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('customer', '[\'kʌstəmər]', 'n.顾客；主顾；<口>家伙', '1. My father asked me to see the customer to the door. 我父亲要我送顾客到门口。 2. The new store across the road has taken away most of my customers. 路那边的那家新店抢走了我的许多主顾。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acute', '[ə\'kjuːt]', 'adj.严重的；敏锐的；急性的；剧烈的', '1. He suffers from acute depression. 他患有严重的抑郁症。 2. This area has an acute shortage of water. 这个地方缺水严重。 3. She has acute hearing. 她有很敏锐的听力。 4. The doctor said that you had acute appendicitis. 医生说您患的是急性阑尾炎。', '副词: acutely 名词: acuteness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('junk', '[dʒʌŋk]', 'n.垃圾；废旧杂物；中国平底帆船 vt.丢弃', '1. Eating too much junk food is bad for your health. 垃圾食品吃得太多对健康有害。 2. I will throw away all of my useless junk. 我会扔掉我所有无用的垃圾。 3. The junk was piled up in the basement. 垃圾被堆放在地下室。 4. She likes to pick up some interesting junk in junk shops. 她喜欢在旧货店买些有趣的旧货。 5. I suggest you junk the old car and buy a new one. 我建议你把旧车扔了,买一辆新的吧。', '过去式: junked 过去分词: junked 现在分词: junking 第三人称单数: junks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slide', '[slaɪd]', 'vi.滑动；下滑；滑入；悄悄地溜走 vt.使滑动 n.幻灯片；滑坡；滑动；雪崩', '1. If you pull this lever, the roof will slide back. 拉一下这根杆,顶就往后滑动。 2. The book slid off my knee. 书从我膝上滑落。 3. House values may begin to slide. 房价可能开始逐渐下降了。 4. I had to slide into base to avoid the tag. 我必须滑上垒以免被触杀。 5. We are to slide the box by exerting a force on it. 我们对箱子施加作用力，使它滑动。 6. After you type your comment you can move it around on the slide. 键入批注后,您可以在幻灯片中移动批注。', '过去式: slid 过去分词: slid 现在分词: sliding 第三人称单数: slides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('correlate', '[\'kɔːrəleɪt]', 'vt.使相互关联 vi.关联 n.相关物', '1. Research workers find it hard to correlate the two sets of figures. 研究人员发现很难使这两组数字互相关连。 2. We can often correlate age with frequency of illness. 年龄的大小往往与发病率有关。 3. The results of this experiment do not correlate with the results of earlier ones. 这次试验的结果与以往试验的结果毫不相干。 4. Hatred is a correlate of love. 恨与爱是互相关联的。', '过去式: correlated 过去分词: correlated 现在分词: correlating 第三人称单数: correlates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('previous', '[\'priːviəs]', 'adj.以前的；先于；在 ... 之前', '1. His previous attempts had been unsuccessful. 他以前的尝试没有成功。 2. It happened previous to his arrival there. 事件发生于他到那儿以前。 3. You must collect enough materials previous to your writing. 你在写作之前必须收集好足够的材料。', '副词: previously 名词: previousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exist', '[ɪɡ\'zɪst]', 'v.存在；生存；活着', '1. Most scientists believe that water doesn\'t exist on the surface of the moon. 多数科学家认为,月球表面不存在水。 2. That department has ceased to exist. 那部门已不复存在。 3. Man cannot exist without air. 没有空气人就不能生存。 4. The old lady exists only on rice coffee and bread. 老太太仅靠咖啡面包生活。', '过去式: existed 过去分词: existed 现在分词: existing 第三人称单数: exists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eighty', '[\'eɪti]', 'num.八十', '1. The old man was on the verge of eighty. 那老人已年近八十。 2. His grandfather must now be getting on for eighty. 他祖父现在一定快八十岁了。', '名词复数: eighties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('manufacture', '[ˌmænju\'fæktʃər]', 'v.（手工）制造；捏造 n.制造；制造业；（复）产品', '1. This firm manufactures cars. 这家公司生产汽车。 2. We manufacture various types of machine tools. 我公司生产各种型号的机床。 3. You will have to manufacture some kind of excuse. 你得找些借口。 4. She manufactured a false story to hide the facts. 她编 造瞎话以掩盖事实。 5. The manufacture of these small components is expensive. 制造这些小部件是非常昂贵的。', '形容词: manufacturable 名词: manufacturing 过去式: manufactured 过去分词: manufactured 现在分词: manufacturing 第三人称单数: manufactures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poverty', '[\'pɑːvərti]', 'n.贫困；贫乏；劣质', '1. People in this area were ground down by hunger and poverty. 这个地区的人们受着饥饿和贫穷的折磨。 2. The man lived in poverty after his unemployment. 这人失业后就生活在贫困之中。 3. Poverty reduced him to begging. 贫穷迫使他行乞。 4. They were handicapped by (a) poverty of resources. 他们因资源短缺处境窘迫。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lifetime', '[\'laɪftaɪm]', 'n.一生；终身；寿命；使用期限', '1. He met with many a setback in his lifetime. 他一生中遭到过许多挫折。 2. The century plant blooms only once in its lifetime. 龙舌兰在其一生中只开一次花。 3. Learning is the enterprise of a lifetime. 学习是终身的事业。 4. These experiences can help make saving money a lifetime habit. 这些经历能使存钱成为终身的习惯。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('manage', '[\'mænɪdʒ]', 'v.管理；经营；做成；设法对付；提供；有空', '1. He managed the company when his father was away. 他父亲离开的时候,由他管理公司。 2. The success of the restaurant lies in that it is well managed. 这个餐厅的成功在于它的完善经营。 3. I shall be able to manage it without help. 我一个人能行。 4. His wife knows how to manage him when he is angry. 他的妻子知道在他生气时怎么对付他。', '过去式: managed 过去分词: managed 现在分词: managing 第三人称单数: manages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dictation', '[dɪk\'teɪʃn]', 'n.听写；口述；命令', '1. The teacher gave the pupils dictation. 教师让学生听写。 2. We have a dictation every English class. 每次上英语课我们都进行听写测验。 3. I hated it if I ever had to take dictation from him. 如果我总是不得不作他的口授记录员，我会感到讨厌的。 4. The pupils wrote at their teacher\'s dictation. 学生按照老师的口述写下来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sake', '[seɪk]', 'n.理由；缘故；目的；利益', '1. He is away all year for the sake of his work. 因工作关系，他整年出门在外。 2. You should take care of your niece for the sake of your sister. 看在姐妹的份上，你应该照顾你的侄女。 3. Never do wrong for the sake of money. 绝不要为金钱而做坏事。 4. It\'s the company\'s policy to sacrifice short-term profits for the sake of long-term growth. 为长期发展而牺牲短期利润是公司的方针。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bet', '[bet]', 'v.打赌；确信无疑 n.赌注；确信', '1. He bet $50 that his horse would win. 他拿50美元打赌，说他的马将会赢。 2. I bet they are making a pile out of the deal. 我肯定他们这笔生意一定赚大钱。 3. I bet that he\'s lost all his money in the gamble. 我肯定他在赌博中输掉了所有的钱。 4. I ventured a small bet on the horse. 我在那匹马上下了一小笔赌注。', '过去式: bet/betted 过去分词: bet/betted 现在分词: betting 第三人称单数: bets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('big', '[bɪɡ]', 'adj.大的；重要的；有雄心的；受欢迎的 adv.宏大地；夸大地；成功地 n.杰出的组织和个人', '1. New York is a big commercial city. 纽约是一座大的商业城市。 2. His business yields big profits. 他的生意带来巨大的利润。 3. Don\'t cry, you are a big boy now. 别哭，你现在已经是大男孩了。 4. The big moment has come at last! 重要的时刻终于到来了！ 5. You need to think big(= aim to achieve a lot). 你要敢想。 6. With that new promotion he\'s now one of the bigs in the company. 通过那次得晋升，他现在是公司的杰出员工之一。', '形容词: biggish 副词: bigly 比较级: bigger 最高级: biggest 名词: bigness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nonetheless', '[ˌnʌnðə\'les]', 'adv.尽管如此(仍然)', '1. Though he\'s fool, I like him nonetheless. 虽然他很笨, 我仍然喜欢他。 2. Nonetheless, the science is pushing forward at a rapid pace. 尽管如此，研究正在迅速向前推进。 3. There are possible risks, but nonetheless, we feel it\'s a sound investment. 有可能存在危险,但是我们仍然感到这是可靠的投资。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sunset', '[\'sʌnset]', 'n.日落；衰落时期（尤指人的晚年）', '1. It is seen in the sky after sunset. 日落後可在天空中看到它。 2. By sunset we had covered thirty miles. 到日落的时候，我们已走了三十英里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('excerpt', '[\'eksɜːrpt]', 'n.摘录 vt.摘录；引用', '1. This is an excerpt from a novel. 这是一部小说的摘录。 2. I\'ve seen a short excerpt from the film on television. 我在电视上看过这部影片的片段。 3. You can excerpt passages from a book. 你可以从一本书中摘录几段。 4. Can you excerpt something from the newspaper? 你能从报纸上选录些东西吗?', '过去式: excerpted 过去分词: excerpted 现在分词: excerpting 第三人称单数: excerpts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invisible', '[ɪn\'vɪzəbl]', 'adj.看不见的；无形的 n.隐形人(或物)', '1. Some stars are invisible to the naked eye. 有些星体肉眼是看不见的。 2. Germs are invisible to the naked eye. 细菌用肉眼看不见。 3. The mends were almost invisible. 修补过的地方几乎看不出来。 4. Aunt Harriet presided over an invisible army of servants that continuously scrubbed, cleaned, and published. 姑母哈丽特支配着一大群看不见的仆人，他们不停地刷洗、打扫和擦拭。 5. Her fantasy is to become invisible. 她的幻想是变成隐形人。', '副词: invisibly 名词: invisibility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('homework', '[\'hoʊmwɜːrk]', 'n.家庭作业', '1. He has done only a fraction of his homework. 他只做了家庭作业的一小部分。 2. I must finish my homework first. 我必须首先做完家庭作业。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bracket', '[\'brækɪt]', 'n.档次；括号；支架 vt.支撑；放在括号内；归入一类', '1. Their incomes are brought into a higher bracket. 他们的收入已进入一个较高的等级段。 2. Put your name in brackets at the top of each page. 把你的名字填写在每页上端的括号内。 3. The worker fixed a bracket on the wall. 工人在墙上固定了一个支架。 4. You\'d better bracket those shelves with two-by-fours. 你最好用截面为2英寸×4英寸的木材为那些架子做托架。', '过去式: bracketed 过去分词: bracketed 现在分词: bracketing 第三人称单数: brackets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stock', '[stɑːk]', 'n.存货；储备；树干；股票；股份；家畜；血统；汤汁；声望 v.采购；储存；供给；发新芽 adj.惯用的；存货的', '1. We have a large stock of tinned fruit. 我们有大批水果罐头的存货。 2. The grocer\'s has plenty varieties of goods in stock. 杂货商有种类繁多的存货。 3. We need to replenish our stocks of coal. 我们需要再次补充煤的储备。 4. Branches grow from the stock of the tree. 树枝是从树干上生长出来的。 5. We must stock up with food for the holiday. 我们必须采购一些食品以备假期之需。 6. She\'s tired of her husband\'s stock jokes. 她已听厌了丈夫那老一套的俏皮话。', '名词: stockage 过去式: stocked 过去分词: stocked 现在分词: stocking 第三人称单数: stocks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ratio', '[\'reɪʃioʊ]', 'n.比率；比例', '1. The ratios of 1 to 5 and 20 to 100 are the same. 1与5之比和20与100之比相同。 2. Men outnumber women here in the ratio of three to one. 此地男子数量以三比一超过女子。 3. The ratio of schoolboys to schoolgirls is 2 to 1. 男学生和女学生的比例是2比1。 4. The ratio of nursing staff to doctors is 2:1. 护士和医生的比例是2：1.', '名词复数: ratios');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('civilization', '[ˌsɪvələ\'zeɪʃn]', 'n.文明；开化；教养', '1. Chinese civilization is one of the oldest in the world. 中国文化是世界上最古老的文化之一。 2. The civilization of mankind has taken thousands of years. 人类经数千年才文明开化。 3. In some ways, civilization does not seem to have progressed much in the last century. 在某些方面，上个世纪文明似乎进展不大。 4. The civilization of these tribes will take a long time. 这些部落的开化将需很长时间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hurt', '[hɜːrt]', 'vt.损害；伤害；使疼痛 vi.疼痛；造成损失 n.创伤；伤害；打击', '1. The rumors hurt his reputation badly. 流言语大大地损害了他的名誉。 2. She hurt my feelings. 她伤害了我的感情。 3. I do not want to hurt anybody and be hurted by anybody. 我不想伤害任何人,也不想让任何人所伤害。 4. It hurts when I try to move my leg. 当我移动我的腿,感到疼痛。 5. The experience left me with a feeling of deep hurt. 这段经历给我心灵上留下了严重的创伤。', '名词: hurter 过去式: hurt 过去分词: hurt 现在分词: hurting 第三人称单数: hurts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reflection', '[rɪ\'flekʃn]', 'n.倒影；反射；反映；沉思；考虑', '1. The cat felt curious when she saw her own reflection in the mirror. 小猫看到自己在镜子中的倒影，感到很好奇。 2. The moon is bright only by reflection. 月亮靠反射发光。 3. They were studying the reflection of sound waves. 他们在研究声波的反射。 4. His dark looks are a reflection of his unhappiness. 他阴郁的神情是内心苦恼的反映。', '形容词: reflectional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('earn', '[ɜːrn]', 'vt.赚得；赢得；获得', '1. He has earned a lot of money in this month. 这个月他已经赚了好多钱了。 2. He works hard, but he does not earn much money. 他工作很努力，但钱赚得不多。 3. How does she earn her living? 她靠什么谋生？ 4. His skill in negotiating earned him a reputation as a shrewd tactician. 他的谈判技巧使他赢得了精明战略家的名声。', '名词: earner 过去式: earned 过去分词: earned 现在分词: earning 第三人称单数: earns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sketch', '[skɛtʃ]', 'n.速写；素描；草图；概述 v.草拟；速写；(简略地)描绘', '1. He is working up a sketch into a picture. 他正在把一幅速写加工成一幅画。 2. He did a sketch of the ballet dancers. 他为这些芭蕾舞者画了一张素描。 3. He squiggled a sketch on the ground. 他在地上胡乱地画了个草图。 4. They only gave us a sketch of the whole event. 他们只向我们简略地介绍了整个事件。 5. Sadly Mr Obama has repeatedly failed to sketch out how he might go about that. 遗憾的是,奥巴马再一次没能草拟出一份解决这一问题的方案。', '名词: sketcher 过去式: sketched 过去分词: sketched 现在分词: sketching 第三人称单数: sketches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('today', '[tə\'deɪ]', 'n.今天；当今 adv.今天；当今 adj.现在的', '1. Today is my birthday. 今天是我的生日。 2. Today is Thursday. 今天是星期四。 3. The fashions of today change very quickly. 现今的时装式样变换很快。 4. I feel my fingers are all thumbs today. 我觉得我今天笨手笨脚。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chart', '[tʃɑːrt]', 'n.图表；规划图；排行榜 v.制成图表；绘制地图；规划', '1. Can you read the weather chart? 你能看懂气象图吗？ 2. They laid out the chart of their destiny to come. 他们展开了他们未来命运的蓝图。 3. Joyride topped the US chart in spring 1991. 专辑《逍遥游》于1991年春荣登美国排行榜榜首。 4. On the map we chart the course of the river. 我们在地图上标出了该河的流向。', '过去式: charted 过去分词: charted 现在分词: charting 第三人称单数: charts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hawk', '[hɔːk]', 'n.鹰；鹰派人物、主战分子；贪婪的人；清嗓 v.沿街叫卖；散布；鹰扑；放鹰行猎；清嗓', '1. The hawk is hovering overhead. 鹰在头顶上盘旋。 2. The hawk pounced on its prey and carried it off. 那只鹰向那小动物猛扑过去把它叼走了。 3. He is neither a dove nor a hawk, but betwixt and between. 他既不是鸽派，也不是鹰派，而是中间派。 4. In a free market, retailers hawk their wares. 自由市场里商贩们不停地叫卖着。', '形容词: hawkish 副词: hawkishly 名词: hawkishness 过去式: hawked 过去分词: hawked 现在分词: hawking 第三人称单数: hawks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('desire', '[dɪ\'zaɪər]', 'n.渴望；愿望；欲望 v.渴望；向往；要求', '1. I am filled with the desire to go back home. 我心中充满了回家的渴望。 2. Young people have no desire to work for the government. 年轻人没有在政府部门工作的意愿。 3. Her desire to dominate other people has caused trouble in her family. 她想支配他人的欲望在家庭中引起了麻烦。 4. She desires for a breakthrough in her research. 她渴望自己的研究能够出现突破。', '名词: desirer 过去式: desired 过去分词: desired 现在分词: desiring 第三人称单数: desires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heat', '[hiːt]', 'n.热度；热；热烈；激烈；发烧 v.(使)变热；(使)激动', '1. Turn the heat down or your cake will burn. 把热度调低吧,要不蛋糕就要糊了。 2. I can\'t walk about in this heat. 我不能在这种酷热下走路。 3. Water is changed into steam by heat and into ice by cold. 水加热则成为蒸汽，冷却则成为冰。 4. So desert should take heat with cereus. 所以沙漠应该为仙人掌而热烈。 5. We\'ll heat some water to wash clothes. 我们会热点儿水洗衣服。', '过去式: heated 过去分词: heated 现在分词: heating 第三人称单数: heats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('north', '[nɔːrθ]', 'adj.北方的；北的 adv.向北方 n.北方；北', '1. Such fish is rarely met with in the north country. 这种鱼在北方难得看到。 2. North America has the world\'s best climate for wild grapes. 北美的气候是世界上最适合野生葡萄生长的。 3. The river turns north at this point. 这条河从这里转向北方。 4. The river near the woods tends north. 树林边的河流向北方。 5. Our course was straight to the north. 我们是朝正北方向航行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tongue', '[tʌŋ]', 'n.舌头；语言；口才；舌状物 v.舔；用舌吹奏管乐器；发音', '1. The tongue is one of the vocals. 舌头是发声器官之一。 2. The dog\'s tongue was hanging out. 这条狗把舌头伸在外面。 3. English is her mother tongue. 英语是她的母语。 4. He speaks English, but his native tongue is German. 他会说英语，但他的母语是德语。 5. The dog tongued the meat on the ground. 狗用舌头舔了舔地上的肉。', '过去式: tongued 过去分词: tongued 现在分词: tonguing 第三人称单数: tongues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wire', '[\'waɪər]', 'n.金属丝；电线；电报 vt.发电报；装电线；(通过电线)接通；用金属丝把...连一起；电汇', '1. The fabric was displayed on a wired stand. 那种织物陈列在金属制的架子上。 2. The rope was not strong enough, so we used wire. 这根绳子不够结实，所以我们用金属线。 3. The hot wire is caused by overload. 电线发热是由于过载造成的。 4. I sent a wire to my mother this morning. 今天上午我给母亲打了电话。 5. Yon can wire the details to my brother in New York. 你可以将细节电告我在纽约的兄弟。', '形容词: wirable 过去式: wired 过去分词: wired 现在分词: wiring 第三人称单数: wires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tale', '[teɪl]', 'n.故事；叙述；传说 v.谈论，讲述，搬弄是非；', '1. Their love story sounds like a fairy tale. 他们的爱情故事听起来像童话。 2. This is a tale that wring the heart. 这是个令人心痛的故事。 3. We listened to their tales about life in the Sahara Desert. 我们听他们讲述撒哈拉沙漠的生活经历。 4. We laugh over this tale, but it\'s becoming almost as true of people. 我们笑着谈论此则故事，但对人类来说，情形也差不多一样。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oar', '[ɔːr]', 'n.桨；橹；划手 v.划行', '1. In dragon boat rowing each person has one oar. 划龙舟时每个人都拿着一枝桨。 2. Sometimes an oar is used to steer a boat. 有时桨用以操纵小舟。 3. A rowing or paddling stroke in which the oar or paddle is pushed forward,used to check a boat\'s forward motion or move it backward. 倒浆，把橹或桨向前推以阻止船向前运动或向后移动的一种划船或摇桨方式。', '形容词: oared 过去式: oared 过去分词: oared 现在分词: oaring 第三人称单数: oars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('atmosphere', '[\'ætməsfɪr]', 'n.大气；空气；气氛；气压', '1. The burning of fossil fuels results in the pollution of the atmosphere. 矿物燃料的燃烧导致了大气污染。 2. The atmosphere of the city is very much polluted. 那个城市的空气受到严重污染。 3. The atmosphere is very stuffy here and can we open a window? 这里的空气很闷,咱们能打开一扇窗吗？ 4. The atmosphere changed as soon as she walked in. 她一进来气氛就变了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('entail', '[ɪn\'teɪl]', 'vt.使必需；带来；限定继承 n.限定继承权', '1. This job entails a lot of hard work. 这项工作需要十分努力。 2. It will entail driving a long distance every day. 这意味着每天都要长途开车。 3. The alteration would entail an expenditure of 50 pounds. 此项改变将带来为数五十英磅的花费。 4. He would have sold the property long ago had it not been entailed. 这些财产若非限定继承的话，他早就卖掉了。 5. You allude perhaps to the entail of this estate. 你大概是说产业的继承权问题。', '名词: entailment 过去式: entailed 过去分词: entailed 现在分词: entailing 第三人称单数: entails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whereas', '[ˌwer\'æz]', 'conj.然而；鉴于', '1. Some people like coffee, whereas others like tea. 有人喜欢咖啡,然而也有人喜欢茶。 2. His children are well bred, whereas those of his sister\'s are naughty. 他的孩子很有教养，但他姐姐的孩子却调皮得很。 3. Whereas we want a flat, they would rather live in a house. 我们想住公寓房，而他们却想住一所房子。 4. Whereas the peoples of the colonies have been grieved and burdened with taxes... 鉴于各殖民地民众备受重税负担之苦....', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slot', '[slɑːt]', 'n.狭缝；槽；投币口；时间段；职位；（鹿的）足迹 v.插入；留细长的孔；放置', '1. She placed her card in a slot on the outside the bank. 她在银行外面把她的卡片塞进一条窄缝。 2. A cleaner slot is already reserved. 清洗器插槽已被保留。 3. He inserted a coin into the slot. 他把硬币插入投币口。 4. The best way to accomplish what on the list is to give each task a specific time slot. 完成单子上的各项任务的最好方法是给每项工作留出一个专门的时间。 5. We can slot in the new entry in alphabetical order. 我们可以按照字母顺序将新词条安插进去。', '过去式: slotted 过去分词: slotted 现在分词: slotting 第三人称单数: slots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cream', '[kriːm]', 'n.奶油；乳酪；面霜；精华；米色 v.凝成乳脂；起泡沫；撇去乳脂；提取精华；使成糊状；涂面霜；<俚>彻底打败', '1. She ladled cream over her pudding. 她在布丁上浇了一勺奶油。 2. A dish of strawberries and cream is not to be despised. 一盘草莓加乳酪应该算不差了。 3. This cream will soften up your skin. 这种面霜会使你皮肤柔软。 4. Proverbs are the cream of a nation\'s thought. 谚语是一国的思想精华。 5. Many special schools cream off the highest achievers. 许多专业学校录取了成绩最好的学生。', '过去式: creamed 过去分词: creamed 现在分词: creaming 第三人称单数: creams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('avail', '[ə\'veɪl]', 'v.有利；有助于 n.益处', '1. Such a statement will not avail. 这样的声明没有什么用。 2. It will avail them to dispose of their booty. 转让赃物对他们来说是有利的。 3. His subtlety could not avail him here. 他精明机智在这里无济于事了。 4. I\'m afraid my help didn\'t avail you much. 恐怕我的帮助对你用处不大。 5. He tried and tried but all his efforts were of no avail. 他试了又试，但一切努力都不起作用。', '副词: availingly 过去式: availed 过去分词: availed 现在分词: availing 第三人称单数: avails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lemon', '[\'lemən]', 'n.柠檬；柠檬色；<俚>次品；令人讨厌的人', '1. I like orange more than lemon. 我喜欢桔子更甚于喜欢柠檬。 2. The fish was garnished with slices of lemon. 那盆鱼上配了几片柠檬作为装饰。 3. The Clumber is primarily a white dog with lemon color or orange color markings. 克伦伯猎鹬犬主要颜色是白色，带有柠檬色或橘色斑纹。 4. He just stood there looking like a real lemon. 他只是站在那里，看上去像个地地道道的笨蛋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('homogeneous', '[ˌhoʊmə\'dʒiːniəs]', 'adj.同质的；同种的；相似的', '1. Life in the United States is no longer if it ever was culturally homogeneous. 美国的生活已经不再是，如果它曾经是，同源文化。 2. Japan has a largely homogeneous population. 日本的人口基本上同属一 个种族。 3. More of the hitherto homogeneous societies are becoming plural ones. 越来越多的单一种族社会逐渐变得多元化。', '副词: homogeneously 名词: homogeneousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eventually', '[ɪ\'ventʃuəli]', 'adv.最后；终于', '1. It was a long journey, but we eventually arrived. 旅程很长，但我们最后还是到达了。 2. He struggled with his assailants and eventually drove them off. 他同攻击他的人进行搏斗，最后把他们赶走了。 3. She eventually got back the book she had lent him. 她终于收回了借给他的书。 4. Eventually the fire was under control. 火势终于被控制住了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flush', '[flʌʃ]', 'v.冲洗；发红；将某人赶出 n.脸红；冲洗；（纸牌）同花牌；【计算机】冲洗', '1. Father asked me to flush off the garage floor. 父亲叫我冲洗车库的地板。 2. The toilet won\'t flush properly. 马桶不好冲。 3. Don\'t forget to flush the toilet after use. 用完厕所,不要忘了冲。 4. Mary flushed crimson with embarrassment. 玛丽羞得脸红了。 5. A flush of excitement crept into his face. 兴奋的红晕爬上他的脸。', '比较级: flusher 最高级: flushest 名词: flusher 过去式: flushed 过去分词: flushed 现在分词: flushing 第三人称单数: flushes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wheel', '[wiːl]', 'n.方向盘；车轮；旋转；周期 vi.旋转；转动；改变方向 vt.用车运；转动；给 ... 装轮子', '1. They found her slumped over the steering wheel. 他们发现她倒伏在方向盘上。 2. Nobody can roll back the wheel of history. 没有人能够倒转历史的车轮。 3. The wheel sheared off and fell to the ground. 车轮突然脱落到地上。 4. A wheel must have a shaft on which it may rotate. 一个轮子必须要有轴，这样它才能旋转。 5. The sails of the windmill were wheeling round. 风车的叶轮正在旋转。 6. Will you wheel him away because he can\'t walk? 他不能走路了，你把他推走好吗?', '过去式: wheeled 过去分词: wheeled 现在分词: wheeling 第三人称单数: wheels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('net', '[net]', 'n.网；网状物 adj.净余的；纯粹的', '1. This area has not been covered by the communication net. 这个地区还不在通讯网的覆盖之内。 2. My mother bought a lot of net curtains. 我妈妈买了很多网眼帘布。 3. The net weight of this jar of coffee is 180 grams. 这瓶咖啡净重180克。 4. What do you earn, net of tax? 你完税后净得多少?', '名词: netter 过去式: netted 过去分词: netted 现在分词: netting 第三人称单数: nets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reward', '[rɪ\'wɔːrd]', 'n.报答；赏金；报酬 vt.奖赏；给 ... 报酬', '1. An act of kindness deserves a reward. 做好事,当然要有报答。 2. By rights, half the reward should be mine. 按理说，有一半奖赏应该是我的。 3. You have received a just reward. 你已得到了应有的报酬。 4. They rewarded the winners with gifts of fruits and flowers. 他们奖给优胜者一些水果和鲜花。', '形容词: rewardable 名词: rewarder 过去式: rewarded 过去分词: rewarded 现在分词: rewarding 第三人称单数: rewards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('direction', '[də\'rekʃn]', 'n.方向；指导；用法说明；趋势；目标；管理', '1. Which direction does your room face? 你的房间面向哪个方向？ 2. The investigation was carried out under the direction of a senior police officer. 调查是在一位高级警官的指导下进行的。 3. Simple directions for assembling the model are printed on the box. 盒上印有装配模型的简要说明。 4. That is the present direction of government thinking. 这就是如今政府考虑问题的取向.', '形容词: directionless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thousand', '[\'θaʊznd]', 'n.<数字>千 n.【C】成千上万；许许多多', '1. Thousands of spectators watched the sailing. 数千名观众观看了这次游艇比赛。 2. I am a thousand winds that blow. 我是扬起千千遍遍的风. 3. Thousand probabilities do not make one truth. 无数的可能也不能成就一个事实。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('introduce', '[ˌɪntrə\'duːs]', 'vt.介绍；引进；采用；提出；提倡；放入', '1. She introduced me to her friend. 她把我介绍给她的朋友。 2. Excuse me, may I take the opportunity to introduce myself as an interpreter? 作为译员,我可以冒昧自我介绍一下吗? 3. Introduce new ideas into a business. 引进新观念于一事业。 4. And it must introduce democratic reforms. 而且必须引进民主改革。', '形容词: introducible 名词: introducer 过去式: introduced 过去分词: introduced 现在分词: introducing 第三人称单数: introduces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gross', '[ɡroʊs]', 'adj.总的；粗鲁的；公然的；荒唐的；令人讨厌的 n.总量；总额 vt.总共赚得 adv.总共地', '1. The gross national product had increased 5 percent last year. 去年的国民生产总值提高了百分之五。 2. You can tell from his gross language that the man was uneducated. 从他那粗俗的语言可以看出，这个人没受过教育。 3. They were accused of gross negligence. 他们因公然渎职而被指控。 4. That is a gross distortion of the truth. 这是对真相的荒唐歪曲。 5. The goods are to be sold by the gross. 这些货物是要趸批出售的。 6. The new movie grossed an estimated $36.4 million at the box office. 这部新电影总共收获了3640万美元的票房成绩。 7. He earned $60,000 gross. 他总共赚了6万美元。', '副词: grossly 比较级: grosser 最高级: grossest 名词: grosser 过去式: grossed 过去分词: grossed 现在分词: grossing 第三人称单数: grosses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('concept', '[\'kɑːnsept]', 'n.观念；概念；想法', '1. I can not understand such an abstract concept. 我无法理解如此抽象的观念。 2. He presented a new concept of the origins of the universe. 他提出了一种宇宙起源的新概念。 3. We had no concept that this tiny mistake would ruin the whole plan. 我们完全没有想到这个小小的失误会毁掉整个计划。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chapter', '[\'tʃæptər]', 'n.章；回；篇', '1. One of the funniest episodes in the book occurs in chapter 6. 书中最有趣的情节是在第6章。 2. He has got prepared to write a new chapter. 他已经准备动手写新的一章。 3. Let us revert to the earlier part of the chapter. 让我们回到本章的前面部分。 4. Chapter IV is about anaphora of third person pronouns. 第四章，第三人称代词回指研究。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cabin', '[\'kæbɪn]', 'n.船舱；机舱；小木屋 vt.抑制 vi.住在小屋', '1. He made out of the cabin on hearing the siren. 他一听到汽笛声就立即走出船舱。 2. Fine. Can you let me have a cabin for two? 好的，能给我订一间二人船舱吗? 3. My cabin is on E deck. 我的舱位在E层甲板。 4. Cabin light will be dim for takeoff. 机舱灯将会因飞机起飞而变暗。 5. The criminal was cabined all the day. 这个犯人整天受到限制。 6. The old man cabined in the forest. 这位老人住在森林的小屋里。', '过去式: cabined 过去分词: cabined 现在分词: cabining 第三人称单数: cabins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overhear', '[ˌoʊvər\'hɪr]', 'v.无意中听到；偷听', '1. I managed to overhear a few interesting snippets of information. 我设法偷听到一点零星有趣的消息。 2. People say in the Tanabata night, can see the cowherd meet, or in the Milky Way under the melon and fruit can overhear in heaven when they meet silently whispers. 人们传说在七夕的夜晚，抬头可以看到牛郎织女的银河相会，或在瓜果架下可偷听到两人在天上相会时的脉脉情话。', '名词: overhearer 过去式: overheard 过去分词: overheard 现在分词: overhearing 第三人称单数: overhears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('request', '[rɪ\'kwest]', 'n.请求；要求 vt.请求；要求', '1. I will oblige any sincere request. 我会答应任何诚意的请求。 2. His answer to my request was a negative. 我的请求遭到了他的拒绝。 3. Your request will be dealt with in due course. 你的要求将在适当时机予以处理。 4. I bought it at your request. 我应你的要求买下来。 5. We request you to deduct our commission from the invoice. 我们请求你方从发票中扣除我们的佣金。', '名词: requester 过去式: requested 过去分词: requested 现在分词: requesting 第三人称单数: requests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enough', '[ɪ\'nʌf]', 'adj.足够的 adv.足够地；充分地；相当；尚 pron.足够', '1. I haven\'t enough time for reading. 我没有足够的时间读书。 2. He has enough money (=money enough) to buy a car. 他有足够的钱买一辆汽车。 3. John\'s old enough to take care of himself. 约翰长大了,能照顾自己了。 4. He is brave enough to face dangers. 他很勇敢,足以面对各种危险。 5. I\'ve had enough of that. 我真受够了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('renovate', '[\'renəveɪt]', 'vt.修理；翻新；革新；刷新', '1. They are going to renovate the old furniture. 他们准备将旧家具整修一番。 2. I\'ve decided to renovate the garden next year. 我准备明年把这座庭园修葺一下。 3. We purchase your technology chiefly in order to renovate our old equipment. 我们购买你们的技术，主要是为了改造我们的旧设备。 4. It cost much to renovate old college buildings at the University of Chang Jiang. 翻新长江大学的旧校舍花费很大。', '名词: renovation 过去式: renovated 过去分词: renovated 现在分词: renovating 第三人称单数: renovates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('niece', '[niːs]', 'n.侄女；外甥女；教士的私生女', '1. Her niece is wearing a bright yellowish skirt. 她的侄女穿著一条鲜明的淡黄色裙子。 2. My niece has practiced ballet for six years. 我侄女已练了六年芭蕾舞了。 3. My niece was left in my trust for the weekend. 我受托周末照顾我的外甥女。 4. Nancy is staying with her niece for the moment. 南希暂时同她外甥女住在一起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recommend', '[ˌrekə\'mend]', 'vt.推荐；建议；劝告；使受欢迎；使可取', '1. Can you recommend me some new books on this subject? 你能推荐一些有关这个学科的新书给我吗? 2. I should recommend it as a useful reference book. 我愿意推荐它作为一本有用的参考书。 3. I recommend you to buy this dictionary and that tape. 我建议你买这本字典和那盒磁带。 4. I recommend that you inquire about the job. 我建议你打听一下这项工作。', '形容词: recommendable 名词: recommender 过去式: recommended 过去分词: recommended 现在分词: recommending 第三人称单数: recommends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('generous', '[\'dʒenərəs]', 'adj.慷慨的；宽宏大量的；丰厚的；丰盛的；味浓的', '1. She was always very generous in her charity. 她行善时总是很慷慨。 2. Such generous actions stamp him as a man of honour. 他的这些慷慨行为表明他是个君子。 3. I regret having been so generous to that scoundrel. 我后悔不该对那坏家伙如此宽宏大量。 4. I am doubly indebted to you-- for the party and for your generous gift! 你为我操办欢送会并赠送厚礼,这样的深情厚谊我铭记在心。', '副词: generously 名词: generousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('republic', '[rɪ\'pʌblɪk]', 'n.共和国；共和政体', '1. He was one of the architects of the republic. 他是这个共和国的缔造者之一。 2. Back to our Republic of Singapore. 回到我们新加坡共和国。 3. In what ways is a republic more desirable than a principality? 共和政体为何比君主政体更令人向往？ 4. In a republic, that paradise of debility, the politician is a petty tyrant who obeys the laws. 在一个共和政体，那是衰弱者的天堂，政治家是一个服从法律的小暴君。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('concert', '[\'kɑːnsərt]', 'n.音乐会；一致；和谐 vt.协定；协同安排 vi.合作', '1. The concert will be given on Saturday. 音乐会将于星期六举行。 2. It is good to go to a concert for a change. 到音乐会去换换环境比较好。 3. The newspaper gave much publicity to the concert. 报纸对这次音乐会进行了充分报道。 4. They did not act in concert with one another. 他们的行动互不协调。 5. We will get together to concert our differences. 我们将聚集一起协调分歧。 6. He refused to concert with his partners. 他拒绝和他的伙伴们合作。', '过去式: concerted 过去分词: concerted 现在分词: concerting 第三人称单数: concerts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rich', '[rɪtʃ]', 'adj.富有的；富饶的；丰富的', '1. He is a rich man. 他是一个富有的人。 2. The rich man left his son nothing in the will. 那位富翁在遗嘱中什么都没给他儿子留下。 3. Our country is a rich land. 我们是一个富饶的国家。 4. He has gained rich experience in these years. 这些年来，他取得了丰富的经验。', '副词: richly 比较级: richer 最高级: richest 名词: richness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peak', '[piːk]', 'n.尖端；山顶；顶峰 v.达到顶峰；使处于顶点 vi.消瘦', '1. In Yersa I noticed a spike on the peak of the pyramid-shaped roof of a church. 在叶拉萨村,我发现一座教堂的金字塔屋顶的尖端有一颗尖钉。 2. The mountain peaks are covered with snow all year. 山顶上终年积雪。 3. Many mountaineers have reached that mountain peak. 许多登山家都登上过那座大山的顶峰。 4. Tourism is at its peak in August. 旅游业在八月份达到高峰。 5. Primary school enrolment will peak this year. 今年小学入学人数将达到最高峰。', '过去式: peaked 过去分词: peaked 现在分词: peaking 第三人称单数: peaks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('passport', '[\'pæspɔːrt]', 'n.护照；手段', '1. Show me your passport, please. 请出示护照。 2. My passport has been transacted. 我的护照已经办完了。 3. The police released him but, significantly, they didn\'t give him back his passport. 警方释放了他，但是没有把护照还给他，这是有特殊用意的。 4. He views boxing as his passport out of poverty. 他把拳击看作自己摆脱贫困的手段。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cupboard', '[\'kʌbərd]', 'n.碗橱；衣柜；<英>壁橱', '1. I put the dishes in the cupboard. 我把菜放在碗橱里。 2. He stored foods in his cupboard. 他把食品存放在碗橱里。 3. All our glass and china is kept in the cupboard. 我们所有的玻璃和陶瓷器皿都放在柜橱里。 4. In the dark he ran up against a cupboard. 他在黑暗中撞着了一只碗橱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bump', '[bʌmp]', 'v.碰撞；颠簸而行；提高 n.肿块；撞击；表面隆起 adv.突然的；猛烈的', '1. I\'ve bumped my knee on the wall. 我的膝盖撞上了墙壁。 2. I am so sorry to bump into you. 对不起，我撞到你了。 3. The old bus bumped along the mountain road. 旧公共汽车沿著山路颠簸行驶。 4. We bumped up and down along the gravel path. 我们沿砾石小路颠簸而行。 5. She got a bump on her head. 她头上撞起了一个包。', '过去式: bumped 过去分词: bumped 现在分词: bumping 第三人称单数: bumps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invasion', '[ɪn\'veɪʒn]', 'n.侵略；侵入', '1. The invasion force was annihilated. 侵略军被消灭了。 2. The regiment covered itself with glory in the invasion battle. 该团在反侵略的战斗中赫赫有名。 3. NATO\'s invasion of this independent country is a brutal violation of human rights. 北约对这个独立的国家的侵略是对人权的野蛮侵犯。 4. They are determined to resist invasion. 他们决定抵抗入侵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reading', '[\'riːdɪŋ]', 'n.阅读；读物；读数；理解；异文 动词read的现在分词.', '1. He spent all his time reading. 他把全部时间都花在阅读上。 2. I have benefited a lot from extensive reading. 广泛的阅读使我受益匪浅。 3. That book is not healthy reading for a child. 对孩子来说那书不是本健康读物。 4. I took some light reading for the train journey. 我带了些轻松的读物乘火车消遣。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ray', '[reɪ]', 'n.光线；射线；辐射 vi.发光；辐射 vt.释放射线；用光线装饰 n.[动]鳐 Ray. n.雷（人名）', '1. My eyes are blind by the direct ray of light. 在光线的直射下，我看不清楚东西。 2. He focused the sun\'s ray on a piece of paper with a burning-glass. 他用一面凸透镜把阳光在纸上聚成焦点。 3. X ray is increasingly used in industry as well. 在工业中X射线也得到了广泛应用。 4. Besides, a global ray-tube tracing method is presented, which is to trace the global wave tubes instead of the many small ray tubes for simulating wave propagations in urban areas. 另外，本论文提出广射线柱追踪法，其中乃是追踪整体射向建筑物表面之辐射电波，有别于一般射线追踪法将发射天线的辐射电波以多个小射线柱来模拟。 5. As time went on,his intelligence rayed out more brightly. 随着时间的推移，他的智慧之光愈加灿烂夺目。 6. The ncident comes just weeks after Crocodile Hunter Steve Irwin died after being stung by a ray. 这场意外发生在鳄鱼捕手史蒂夫艾文被鳐刺死的数星期之后。 7. Ray take a gulp of coffee and rushed out of the room. 雷喝了一大口咖啡，接着便冲出了房间。', '过去式: rayed 过去分词: rayed 现在分词: raying 第三人称单数: rays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hunger', '[\'hʌŋɡər]', 'n. 饥饿； 渴望 v. 饿； 渴望； 使 ... 饥饿', '1. He was goaded by hunger into stealing. 他为饥饿所迫而行窃。 2. I had experienced the pangs of hunger. 我曾经历过饥饿的折磨。 3. His hunger for knowledge drove him to the library. 他对求知的强烈渴望驱使他上图书馆。 4. My hunger for magic is clouding my judgement! 我对魔法的渴望已经淡化了我的判断力。 5. Hunger gives relish to simple food. 肚子饿时吃什么都香。', '过去式: hungered 过去分词: hungered 现在分词: hungering 第三人称单数: hungers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rent', '[rent]', 'n.租金 v.租用；出租 动词rend的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The rent is due at the end of each quarter. 缴纳租金以每季度末为期限。 2. They let the house to me at a rent of 100 dollars a month. 他们把房子租给我，每月租金一百美元。 3. I rent a room from her. 我向她租了一个房间。 4. I\'d like to rent a car for just one day. 我想租一部车，一天即可。', '形容词: rentable 名词: rentability 过去式: rented 过去分词: rented 现在分词: renting 第三人称单数: rents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('continue', '[kən\'tɪnjuː]', 'v.继续；连续；维持；持续', '1. He is to continue as manager. 他要继续当经理。 2. They continued down until they came to some pockets of natural gas. 他们继续往下钻，终於找到了一些天然气的气阱。 3. She continued as mayor for a second term. 她连任了一期市长 4. We will continue with the payments for another year. 我们这样的报酬还要再维持一年。', '形容词: continuable 名词: continuer 过去式: continued 过去分词: continued 现在分词: continuing 第三人称单数: continues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hunt', '[hʌnt]', 'v.狩猎；打猎；搜索 n.狩猎；追捕；搜寻', '1. The huntsman and I hunt the animals out of the garden. 猎人和我把动物赶出花园。 2. Wolves hunt in packs. 狼总是成群猎食。 3. They used to hunt with bows and arrows. 他们过去都是用弓箭打猎。 4. He goes out on the weekends to hunt for game. 他每周末都外出打猎。 5. The dog was trained to the hunt. 这只狗受过狩猎训练。', '过去式: hunted 过去分词: hunted 现在分词: hunting 第三人称单数: hunts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unify', '[\'juːnɪfaɪ]', 'vt.使统一、使成为一体', '1. The new leader hopes to unify the country. 新领袖希望把国家统一起来。 2. England and Scotland do not have a unified legal system. 英格兰和苏格兰法制不统一.', '形容词: unifiable 名词: unification 过去式: unified 过去分词: unified 现在分词: unifying 第三人称单数: unifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nurture', '[\'nɜːrtʃər]', 'vt.养育；培育；照顾；扶持 n.养育；培育；环境因素', '1. She nurtured the child as if he had been her own. 她把那个孩子当作自己的孩子来教育。 2. Most vegetables we buy in winter are nurtured in the greenhouse. 我们冬天买的大多数蔬菜都是在温室里培育的。 3. We have to care for and nurture the plant first. 我们必须先要照顾灌溉树木。 4. They are best friends and nurture each other. 他们是最好的朋友，并且相互扶持。 5. The child got his nurture from his loving parents. 这个孩子的教育来自他慈爱的双亲。', '名词: nurturer 过去式: nurtured 过去分词: nurtured 现在分词: nurturing 第三人称单数: nurtures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conscience', '[\'kɑːnʃəns]', 'n.良心；是非之心；顾忌', '1. She was afflicted with conscience. 她受良心责备。 2. The thief\'s conscience smote him. 那个贼突然良心发现。 3. She gave him back the money she\'d stolen for the sake of her conscience. 为了不受良心的谴责，她把从他那偷来的钱还给他了。 4. This is a document that serves as the nation\'s conscience. 这是一份表明民族道德准则的文件。', '形容词: conscienceless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rebellion', '[rɪ\'beljən]', 'n.叛乱；反抗', '1. The rebellion was soon stamped on by the army. 军队很快平息了叛乱。 2. The rebellion was crushed by government forces. 政府军已把叛乱镇压下去。 3. The government has just put down a rebellion. 这个国家刚刚镇压了一场叛乱。 4. The people would rise in open rebellion if oppressed by a monarchy. 如果遭到君主制的压迫，人民就会起来反抗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deduce', '[dɪ\'duːs]', 'vt.演绎；推断', '1. He will deduce a conclusion from premises. 从前提推导出结论。 2. If a = b and b = c, we can deduce that a = c. 设a = b，b = c，可以推断a=c。 3. The police were able to deduce where the fugitive was hiding. 警方成功地推断出那逃亡者躲藏的地方。', '形容词: deducible 过去式: deduced 过去分词: deduced 现在分词: deducing 第三人称单数: deduces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ache', '[eɪk]', 'n.痛；隐痛 vi.渴望；痛', '1. There was a little ache in her fancy of all he described. 她想象着他所描绘的一切，心里不禁有些刺痛。 2. You\'ll make your back ache if you carry those heavy buckets. 如果你背那些沉重的桶，你的背会痛的。 3. He felt a dull ache in his shoulder. 他感到肩膀隐隐作痛。 4. Even though women may ache for love, they carry around an inner evaluator who asks, Can I count on this man? 即使女人渴望爱情，她们也会在内心自问：“我能信赖这个男人吗?', '过去式: ached 过去分词: ached 现在分词: aching 第三人称单数: aches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('age', '[eɪdʒ]', 'n.年龄；时代；时期；长时间 v.（使）变老；（使）陈化', '1. What is your age? 你多大年纪？ 2. The child is at an impressionable age. 这孩子正处于易受影响的年龄。 3. We are living in the age of technology. 我们生活在工业技术时代。 4. Rome was in its prime in the age of Augustus. 罗马帝国的全盛期是在奥古斯都时代。 5. Anxiety ages us. 忧虑催人老。', '名词: ager 过去式: aged 过去分词: aged 现在分词: aging 第三人称单数: ages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resistance', '[rɪ\'zɪstəns]', 'n.抵抗；抵触；反对；阻力 n.[电]阻抗', '1. The strategy was designed to wear down the enemy\'s resistance. 这一策略旨在逐步削弱敌人的抵抗力。 2. Her resistance to the proposal has crumpled. 她对这个建议的抵触情绪已化为乌有了。 3. There has been a lot of resistance to this new law. 反对这项新法律的人很多。 4. We anticipated that we would meet a certain amount of resistance to our plan. 我们预料到我们的计划会遇到一些人的反对。 5. Copper has less resistance than lead. 铜的电阻比铅的小。', '形容词: resistant');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bolt', '[boʊlt]', 'n.门闩；螺栓；一卷布；弩箭 v.（突然）逃离；闩住；狼吞虎咽；用螺栓固定 adv.挺直地', '1. The bolt slotted smoothly into place. 插销很容易就插上了。 2. We need an eye bolt to fit this valve. 我们需要一个有眼螺栓来固定这个阀门。 3. I saw a man bolt out of our backyard. 我看到一个男人从我们家的后院窜出去。 4. The frightened boy bolted all the doors and windows. 这个吓坏了的孩子闩上了所有的门窗。 5. It annoys me if a lamppost is not bolt upright. 如果灯杆不是笔直的,我就看不过去。', '过去式: bolted 过去分词: bolted 现在分词: bolting 第三人称单数: bolts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('short', '[ʃɔːrt]', 'adj.短的；矮的；短期的；短缺的；简略的；粗暴无礼的；[语]短音的 adv.缺少；未达到；半中间(打断)；过早地(终止) n.<英口>烈酒；电影短片；[电]短路 v.(使)短路', '1. You\'ve cut my hair very short. 你把我头发剪得太短了。 2. In contrast with his brothers, Tom is rather short. 与几位兄弟相比,汤姆的个子相当矮。 3. Let\'s take a short break for lunch. 让我们休息一会儿，去吃午饭。 4. These goods are in short supply; the price will be high. 这些商品现正供应不足，价格会上涨。 5. The children mustn\'t go short of food. 孩子们不可以缺少食物。', '比较级: shorter 最高级: shortest 名词: shortness 过去式: shorted 过去分词: shorted 现在分词: shorting 第三人称单数: shorts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lazy', '[\'leɪzi]', 'adj.懒惰的；懒散的', '1. Her lazy husband is a millstone round her neck. 她的懒丈夫成了她的一个包袱。 2. He is so lazy; he could do with a good kick up the rear. 他这个人太懒惰，真想在他屁股上踢一脚。 3. The lazy girl is dreaming of marrying a millionaire and therefore won\'t do any work. 这个懒惰的女孩正梦想着嫁给一个有钱人，从此不再工作。 4. It was a lazy, breezy summer afternoon. 这是一个懒散的，微风风的夏日下午。', '副词: lazily 比较级: lazier 最高级: laziest 名词: laziness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('a', '[ə]', 'art.一(个)；每一(个)；任一(个) n.英语字母表的第一个字母；学业成绩得优者；表示“最好”的符号', '1. There is a pen on the table. 桌子上有一支笔。 2. We have a problem. 我们有个问题。 3. I can only carry two at a time. 我一次只能带两个。 4. Let\'s go to a Chinese restaurant. 我们去一家中餐餐馆。', '名词复数: a\'s');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('meet', '[miːt]', 'v.遇见；满足 n.运动会；集会 adj.合适的', '1. I chanced to meet an old friend in the park today. 今天我在公园碰巧遇见一位老朋友。 2. She is the girl whom you meet at the airport. 她就是你在机场遇见的那个女孩。 3. Ensure that your request be the fastest meet. 保证你的要求得到最快的满足。 4. What criteria should the memorial meet? 纪念碑要满足那些条件？ 5. The sports meet was postponed because of rain. 运动会因雨延期。 6. It is easy to fall in love when you meet the right person. 当你遇到合适的对象就很容易恋爱。', '副词: meetly 过去式: met 过去分词: met 现在分词: meeting 第三人称单数: meets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reasonable', '[\'riːznəbl]', 'adj.合理的；通情达理的；公平适度的', '1. The management took all reasonable safety precautions. 管理部门采取了一切合理的安全措施。 2. All you need is reasonable doubt. 你所需要的是合理怀疑。 3. You are fortunate to have such a reasonable father. 你有这样一位通情达理的父亲，真是幸运。 4. My mother was always reasonable. 我母亲一向通情达理。', '副词: reasonably 名词: reasonability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beneficial', '[ˌbenɪ\'fɪʃl]', 'adj.有利的；有益的', '1. It\'s a beneficial result to us. 对我们来说那是有利的结果。 2. Word of mouth advertising is the most beneficial. 口碑广告是最有利的。 3. Calcium is beneficial to our bones. 钙对我们的骨骼有益。 4. Fresh air is beneficial to our health. 新鲜空气有益于健康。', '副词: beneficially 名词: beneficialness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('investigate', '[ɪn\'vestɪɡeɪt]', 'v.调查；研究', '1. The police are investigating the murder. 警察正在调查这件谋杀案。 2. We might be able to help you; I\'ll investigate the possibilities. 我们也许能帮助你，我要研究一下这种可能性。', '形容词: investigable 过去式: investigated 过去分词: investigated 现在分词: investigating 第三人称单数: investigates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brittle', '[\'brɪtl]', 'adj.易碎的；尖利的；脆弱的 n.果仁薄脆糖', '1. The ice is brittle as the thin glass. 这些冰像薄的玻璃一样易碎。 2. The pond was covered in a brittle layer of ice. 池塘覆盖了一层易碎的冰。 3. Constant stress has made our nerves brittle. 我们长期处于紧张状态，神经已经吃不消了。 4. The orchestra was brittle in tone. 管弦乐队演奏的曲调尖利刺耳。', '副词: brittlely 比较级: brittler 最高级: brittlest 名词: brittleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('democratic', '[ˌdemə\'krætɪk]', 'adj.民主的；民主党的；大众的', '1. Many people were elected to take part in democratic involvement. 很多人被选举参与民主管理。 2. If we want to live a peaceful and democratic life, we must object to wars. 如果我们要过和平与民主的生活,就必须要反对战争。 3. She ran for office on the Democratic ticket. 她作为民主党的候选人参加竞选。 4. He threw a vote for the Democratic candidate. 他投了民主党总统候选人一票。', '副词: democratically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oxygen', '[\'ɑːksɪdʒən]', 'n.氧；氧气', '1. Water contains hydrogen and oxygen. 水含有氢和氧。 2. Hydrogen and oxygen are gases. 氢和氧是气体。 3. Plants can absorb carbon dioxide and release oxygen. 植物可以吸收二氧化碳释放氧气。 4. Mars is too dry and poor in oxygen. 火星上面过于干燥，并且缺乏氧气。', '形容词: oxygenic 副词: oxygenically 简写符号: O');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('breadth', '[bredθ]', 'n.宽度', '1. The length of the table is twice its breadth. 桌子的长度是它的宽度的两倍。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flow', '[floʊ]', 'n.流动；涨潮；流；流量 vi.流动；涌出；飘动；流畅 vt.淹没', '1. The government is trying to stop the increasing flow of refugees entering the country. 政府正在设法阻止越来越多的难民流入本国。 2. The flow of melted snow cascaded down the mountainside and into the river. 溶化的雪水如瀑布般沿着山崖边泻入河里。 3. I saw the ebb and flow of the sea. 我目睹了海潮的涨落。 4. A free flow of water came from the pipe. 水从管道里通畅地流了出来。 5. This river flowed southwest to the Atlantic Ocean. 这条河流向西南，汇入大西洋。 6. The low grounds along the river are annually flowed. 沿河的低洼地每年都要受淹。', '副词: flowingly 过去式: flowed 过去分词: flowed 现在分词: flowing 第三人称单数: flows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('limitation', '[ˌlɪmɪ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.限制；限度；缺点', '1. The government has imposed limitation on imports. 政府已经对进口加以了限制。 2. There will be no limitation to persons from any specific countries. 并不局限于任何特定国家的国民。 3. Every interest has its own boundary and limitation. 任何利益都有自己的边界和限度。 4. He knows his limitations. 他知道自己的能力有限。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coincidence', '[koʊ\'ɪnsɪdəns]', 'n.巧合；一致；同时发生', '1. What a coincidence! 真是太巧了！ 2. That was a really creepy coincidence. 那样的巧合实在太离奇了。 3. That\'s the most incredible coincidence I\'ve ever heard of! 那是我听说过的最难以置信的巧合！ 4. The plot of the novel relies too much on coincidence to be realistic. 这部小说的情节多靠巧合安排而无真实感。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('may', '[meɪ]', 'aux.可以，能够；可能，也许；祝，愿；会，能 n.[大写] 五月', '1. Well, and who may you be? 那麽，你是谁呢? 2. That might be our taxi. 那辆有可能是我们的计程车。 3. That may be our taxi now! 那辆可能就是我们的计程车了。 4. Might I suggest another time? 我可以建议另找个时间吗？', '过去式: might');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('electrical', '[ɪ\'lektrɪkl]', 'adj.电的；与电有关的', '1. There is a fault in the electrical system. 电路系统出了故障。 2. Now electrical appliances have entered into ordinary families. 现在家用电器已经步入普通家庭。 3. There are some electrical apparatus in the room. 房间里有些电器。 4. Electrical problems may be an issue. 可能会遇到有关电的问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slave', '[sleɪv]', 'n.奴隶；像奴隶般受制的人；【机】从动装置 v.做苦工；做奴隶；拼命干', '1. This slave dreamed of becoming a freeman. 这个奴隶梦想着成为一个自由人。 2. The boy was caught and sold to be a galley slave. 这个男孩被抓住，并被卖到战舰上做奴隶。 3. He is a slave to drink. 他是个酒鬼。 4. Why should I slave away all my life ! 我为什么要辛辛苦苦地干一辈子呀！', '过去式: slaved 过去分词: slaved 现在分词: slaving 第三人称单数: slaves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oneself', '[wʌn\'self]', 'pron.自己；自身', '1. One can congratulate oneself on one\'s victories. 一个人也可以自己庆祝自己的胜利。 2. One should be strict with oneself. 一个人应对自己要求严格。 3. How should my friend safeguard the rights and interests of oneself? 我的朋友该如何维护自身的权益呢? 4. So video license plate is not all-purpose, important still is oneself superintend. 所以视频牌照并不是万能的，重要的还是自身监管。', '异体字: one\'sself');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disappoint', '[ˌdɪsə\'pɔɪnt]', 'v.使失望；使破灭', '1. The result disappointed him. 结果使他失望。 2. Her decision to cancel the concert is bound to disappoint her fans. 她决定取消这场音乐会，肯定会使她的歌迷失望。 3. I am sorry to disappoint your expectations . 我很抱歉使你的希望落空。 4. I\'m sorry to disappoint your plans. 我很抱歉妨碍了你的计划。', '过去式: disappointed 过去分词: disappointed 现在分词: disappointing 第三人称单数: disappoints');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sudden', '[\'sʌdn]', 'adj.突然的；出乎意料的 n.突发之事', '1. His sudden death upset everybody. 他的突然去世使大家深感悲伤。 2. A sudden smile illuminated her face. 突然的微笑使她容光焕发。 3. She was dazzled by her sudden success. 突然的成功使她感到迷惘。 4. He gave me a fright by bursting into a sudden laughter. 他突然大笑起来，吓了我一跳。 5. The boy began crying all of a sudden. 那男孩忽然哭了起来。', '副词: suddenly 名词: suddenness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('burden', '[\'bɜːrdn]', 'n.负担；责任；装载量；主题；[音乐]副歌 v.使负重；装载；烦扰', '1. The burden on his back seemed to be crushing him to the earth. 他背上的重负似乎要把他压倒在地。 2. People on high incomes face a huge tax burden. 高收入的人面临着沉重的纳税负担。 3. The burden of organizing the campaign fell to me. 组织这次活动的责任落到了我头上。 4. I don\'t want to lay a burden on you. 我不想让你承担责任。 5. I don\'t want to burden you with my problem. 我不想让我的问题给你添麻烦。', '过去式: burdened 过去分词: burdened 现在分词: burdening 第三人称单数: burdens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('belt', '[belt]', 'n.腰带；带状物；地带；皮带 vt.用皮带抽打；用带系上；用带标示 vi.疾驰；大声歌唱', '1. He has a brown belt in karate. 他有一条空手道的棕腰带。（他是空手道茶带） 2. A belt of trees grew between the two fields. 两块田之间有一条树木带。 3. As Indonesia lies in the volcanic belt, earthquakes can occur. 由于印尼位于火山地带,因此有发生地震的可能。 4. My trousers only stay up if I wear a belt. 我这条裤子要是不系皮带就往下掉。 5. He strapped the driver with a leather belt. 他用皮带抽打司机。 6. They went belting along the road. 他们沿着马路疾驰而去。', '过去式: belted 过去分词: belted 现在分词: belting 第三人称单数: belts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surpass', '[sər\'pæs]', 'vt.超越；胜过', '1. To be in love is to surpass oneself. 人在爱中超越自我。 2. You seem to surpass yourself in this painting. 你在这幅画的创作上似乎超越了你自己。 3. Her sweetness nothing can surpass. 温柔甜蜜世无双。 4. It is hard to surpass Evans in speed. 要在速度上胜过艾文斯很难。', '过去式: surpassed 过去分词: surpassed 现在分词: surpassing 第三人称单数: surpasses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acceptable', '[ək\'septəbl]', 'adj.合意的；受欢迎的；可接受的', '1. If these terms are not acceptable to you, we may suggest others. 如果你对这些条件不合意，我们可提出别的条件。 2. Compliments are always acceptable. 恭维话总是受欢迎的。 3. Yogurt is a perfectly acceptable substitute for cream in cooking. 酸奶是烹饪用的特别受欢迎的奶油替代品。 4. The solution to this problem is acceptable. 这个问题的解决方案是可接受的。', '副词: acceptably 名词: acceptability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('responsible', '[rɪ\'spɑːnsəbl]', 'adj.有责任的；负责的；责任重大的；可靠的', '1. Who\'s responsible for the terrible mess? 谁应该对这种混乱负责？ 2. As a boy, i know, i was responsible to help her. 作为个男生,我知道,我有责任帮助她。 3. We all think of her as a responsible teacher. 我们都认为她是一位很负责的教师。 4. You are supposed to be responsible for them. 你是应当对他们负责的。', '副词: responsibly 名词: responsibleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('roundabout', '[\'raʊndəbaʊt]', 'adj.绕道的；迂回的 n.环形交叉路口 n.(英)旋转木马 n.紧身短上衣', '1. We drove home by a roundabout route. 我们绕远道驾车回家。 2. The taxi didn\'t go by the direct route, but in a roundabout way. 出租车没有走直路，而是绕道行驶。 3. She suggested it in a very roundabout way. 她很婉转地提出了这个建议。 4. I entered the village by the little roundabout lane. 我由一条迂回曲折的小径进了村。 5. Turn left at the next roundabout. 在下一个环形交叉路口向左转。 6. The kids were pushing the roundabout at a giddy speed. 孩子们推动着旋转平台快得令人眩晕。 7. There was a slight noise behind her and she turned just in time to seize a small boy by the slack of his roundabout and arrest his flight. 这时在她身后传来一声轻微的响声，她转身一把抓住了一个小男孩的短外套的衣角，他想跑都跑不掉了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('straightforward', '[ˌstreɪt\'fɔːrwərd]', 'adj.易懂的；笔直的；坦率的', '1. The instructions are reasonably straightforward. 用法说明还算简单易懂。 2. I wonder if the literature can be put in straightforward Chinese. 我不知道那些说明书能不能译成简明易懂的中文。 3. This book presents an up-to-date, straightforward course for students. 这本书为学生提供了一本最新式的、简明易懂的教程。 4. They took a straightforward route to the lake. 他们走了一条笔直通向湖的路。', '副词: straightforwardly 名词: straightforwardness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pop', '[pɑːp]', 'v.发出(砰的响声)；取出；突然行动；突然出现；爆开；睁大；开枪 n.流行音乐，流行艺术；爆裂声；<美口>爸爸 adj.通俗的；流行的；热门的', '1. The champagne cork popped when he pulled it out. 他拔香槟酒的瓶塞时它砰的一声开了。 2. I must pop round to baker\'s for a loaf of bread. 我得到面包店去买一个面包来。 3. The rabbits popped out as soon as we opened the hutch. 我们一打开兔箱，兔子就突然跑出来了。 4. He seem to pop up in the most unlikely place. 在他似乎绝不可能到的地方,他往往就在那里出现。 5. He likes pop; he doesn\'t care for classic music. 他喜欢流行歌曲，不喜欢古典音乐。 6. We\'ve got many students study pop psychology in our school. 我们学校有很多学生学习通俗心理学。', '过去式: popped 过去分词: popped 现在分词: popping 第三人称单数: pops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('foreign', '[\'fɔːrən]', 'adj.外来的；外国的；异质的；不相符的', '1. Our foreign trade has expanded during recent years. 近年来我们的对外贸易有所增加。 2. As a result, we were able to attract a lot of foreign investment. 结果,我们吸引了大量的外来投资。 3. It\'s not easy to master a foreign language. 掌握一门外语并不容易。 4. He\'s visited many foreign countries and has learnt several foreign languages. 他访问过许多国家，并学会了好几种外语。', '名词: foreignness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discipline', '[\'dɪsəplɪn]', 'n.纪律；训练；学科 vt.训练；惩罚', '1. She is strict in the matter of discipline. 她对纪律的要求是严格的。 2. It takes years of discipline to become a pianist. 要成为钢琴家需经多年训练。 3. Applied linguistics is a new and independent discipline. 应用语言学是一门新兴的独立学科。 4. It showed that they had been well disciplined. 这表明他们受过良好的训练。', '形容词: disciplinal 名词: discipliner 过去式: disciplined 过去分词: disciplined 现在分词: disciplining 第三人称单数: disciplines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('distinguish', '[dɪ\'stɪŋɡwɪʃ]', 'vt.区别；辨认；使显著', '1. Speeches distinguish human beings from animals. 人类和动物的区别在于人会说话。 2. It\'s important to distinguish fact from fiction. 把现实与虚构区分开来是很重要的。 3. The twins were so much alike that it was impossible to distinguish one from the other. 这对孪生子像得使人无法分辨。 4. We should distinguish between right and wrong. 我们应辨别是非。', '形容词: distinguishable 副词: distinguishably 过去式: distinguished 过去分词: distinguished 现在分词: distinguishing 第三人称单数: distinguishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('present', '[\'preznt]', 'n.礼物；现在 adj.出席的；现在的；当前的；存在的 v.提出；赠送；呈现', '1. He bought me a valuable diamond ring as a birthday present. 他给我买了一只贵重的钻戒作生日礼物。 2. I wish to make you a present in token of my gratitude. 我想送你一件礼物，以表示对你的感谢之情。 3. Focusing on the future instead of the present can cripple any activity. 不注意现在只考虑将来就可能做不成任何事。 4. There\'s no certain cure for this illness at present. 现在这种病尚无确实可靠的疗法。 5. He insists on being present. 他一定要出席。 6. He presented quite a new view of the affair. 他对那件事提出了相当新的看法。', '名词: presentness 过去式: presented 过去分词: presented 现在分词: presenting 第三人称单数: presents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('altogether', '[ˌɔːltə\'ɡeðər]', 'adv.总共；完全；总的来说', '1. He bought altogether 500 hectares of land. 他总共买了五百公顷土地。 2. There are ten people altogether. 这里总共有十个人。 3. I am altogether on your side in this matter. 在这个问题上我完全支持你。 4. I dissent altogether from such an unwise idea. 我完全不同意这样愚昧的见解。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('method', '[\'meθəd]', 'n.方法；条理 n.类函数；类成员函数（计算机）', '1. I have a simple and easy method. 我有个简易的方法。 2. New methods of teaching foreign languages are adopted in this institute. 该学院采用新的外语教学法。 3. His book is totally without method. 他写的那本书毫无条理。 4. We must get some method into our office filing. 我们必须把公文归档工作弄出些条理来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('find', '[faɪnd]', 'v.发现；找到；认为；觉得；感到；裁决；判定 n.发现', '1. We have found oil under the North Sea. 我们在北海发现了石油。 2. I think I\'m lost; I can\'t find the bridge. 我想我是迷路了，我找不到那座桥了。 3. He tried to find in the list his own name. 他试图在名单上找到自己的名字。 4. How do you find your new job? 你认为你的新工作怎么样？ 5. Our new babysitter is a real find. 我们新来的临时保姆是难得的好保姆。', '形容词: findable 过去式: found 过去分词: found 现在分词: finding 第三人称单数: finds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spread', '[spred]', 'v.传播；展开；散布；铺开；伸展；涂撒 n.范围；传播；差额；幅度；盛宴', '1. The radio spread the news as soon as the accident happened . 事故一发生,收音机就把这条消息传播出去了。 2. The rumor was widely spread among the crowd. 谣言在人群当中广泛地传播开来。 3. She spread her wings and flew lightly down. 她展开双翅轻轻飞下。 4. I spread my arms as far apart as I could. 我尽可能地将双臂伸展开。 5. The current survey will have a wider geographic spread. 当前的调查将在更广泛的地域范围內进行。', '形容词: spreadable 副词: spreadably 名词: spreadability 过去式: spread 过去分词: spread 现在分词: spreading 第三人称单数: spreads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tiny', '[\'taɪni]', 'adj.极小的；微小的', '1. A tiny fishing boat was drifting slowly along. 一只小小的渔船在缓缓地漂去。 2. We\'re struggling along on a tiny income. 我们依靠极少的收入过活。 3. She has a tiny mole on her cheek. 她面颊上有一颗小痣。 4. The baby\'s dress was beautifully tucked with tiny stitches. 婴儿衫的褶裥打得针脚细密，很漂亮。', '比较级: tinier 最高级: tiniest 名词: tininess');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('should', '[ʃəd]', 'aux.应该；可能；应当；竟然；将要', '1. You should take advantage of it. 你应该好好利用这个机会。 2. It should cost roughly 10. 这大约10英镑。 3. You should give it a try. 你应该试一试。 4. That he should speak to you like that is quite astonishing. 他竟然这样对你说话', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('case', '[keɪs]', 'n.例子；情况；案例；（辩论或诉讼）论据；箱 v.装箱；踩点；仔细检查', '1. Talk of wasting money, my buying this car is a case in point. 谈到浪费钱财,我买这台车就是个恰当的例子。 2. In your case, we are prepared to be lenient. 根据你的情况，我们拟予从宽处理 3. But that is not always the case, sometimes the table can turn. 但事情并不一定都是这样,有时情况会发生改变。 4. The case involved charges of police corruption. 这个案子涉及对警方腐败的控诉。 5. The goods have been cased up for transport. 货物已装箱待运。', '过去式: cased 过去分词: cased 现在分词: casing 第三人称单数: cases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('camera', '[\'kæmərə]', 'n.照相机；摄像机', '1. Her camera strap has broken. 她的照相机吊带断了。 2. This wall will do as a rest for your camera. 这面墙可以作为你照相机的依托。 3. We have a video camera. 我们有一架摄像机。 4. The camera panned slowly across to the door. 镜头慢慢摇向门口。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('literally', '[\'lɪtərəli]', 'adv.逐字地；按照字面上地；不夸张地；正确地；简直', '1. He translated this article literally. 他一字一句地翻译这篇文章。 2. Don\'t read the report literally now, just skim through it. 现在，不要逐字读报告，大致地看一下就可以了。 3. Idioms usually cannot be translated literally in another language. 成语通常不能照字面译成另一种语言。 4. He literally flew into the room. 他简直是飞也似地跑进了房间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('own', '[oʊn]', 'adj.自己的；特有的 n.自己的东西 v.承认；拥有', '1. But I can\'t hold on to my own principles, either. 但是,我也没有能够坚持自己的主张。 2. The writer has his own brand of humour. 这位作家有他独特的幽默感。 3. Children need toys of their own. 儿童需要有自己的玩具。 4. He owns he was wrong. 他承认他错了。', '名词: owner 过去式: owned 过去分词: owned 现在分词: owning 第三人称单数: owns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('laptop', '[\'læptɑːp]', 'n.便携式电脑；笔记本电脑', '1. The laptop is three times more expensive than that desktop. 这台手提电脑比那台台式电脑贵三倍。 2. A laptop would be really useful when I\'m traveling. 外出旅游的时候，笔记本电脑还是很有用的。 3. The cat was biting on the electrical cord to my laptop. 这只猫正在咬我笔记本电脑的电线。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jealous', '[\'dʒeləs]', 'adj.妒忌的；羡慕的；嫉妒的', '1. He was hounded out of his job by jealous rivals. 他受到忌妒他的竞争者的算计而被迫离职。 2. He was said to be jealous of her. 据说是他忌妒她。 3. I was jealous of Mary\'s new bicycle. 我很羡慕玛丽的新自行车。 4. He is jealous of his colleague\'s success. 他嫉妒同事的成功。', '副词: jealously 名词: jealousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('generation', '[ˌdʒenə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.代；（产品类型的）代；产生；繁殖', '1. There is a generation gap between my parents and I. 我父母和我之间有代沟。 2. One generation blows bubbles, and the next breaks them. 前一代人制造出来的空洞理论，下一代人把它们打破。 3. Their visionary ideas are often misunderstood by their own generation. 他们有远见的理想往往招致同时代人的误解。 4. Each generation has its own standards of judgement. 每一代都有它自己的判断标准。', '形容词: generational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('revolt', '[rɪ\'voʊlt]', 'n.叛乱；反抗；反感 v.叛乱；起反感', '1. The revolt was suppressed in a matter of hours. 叛乱在几小时之内就镇压下去了。 2. All North Africa would flame into revolt. 整个北非将激起反抗。 3. Her mere experience and the free out-of-door life of country caused her nature to revolt at such confinement. 她那简单的经验和自由自在的乡村户外生活，使她对这个窒息的地方起了反感。 4. The peasants revolted against their oppressors. 农民们起义反抗他们的压迫者。', '名词: revolter 过去式: revolted 过去分词: revolted 现在分词: revolting 第三人称单数: revolts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('food', '[fud]', 'n.食物；食品', '1. What\'s your favorite food? 你最喜欢的食物是什么？ 2. I prefer vegetarian food. 我喜欢吃素食。 3. The scarcity of food forced prices up. 食物短缺促使物价上涨。 4. They were shoveling food into their mouths. 他们正大口大口地往嘴里塞食物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elapse', '[ɪ\'læps]', 'v.逝去；过去 n.（光阴）逝去', '1. Five months have elapsed since he joined the army. 自从他参军以后,已经五个月了。 2. Three years have elapsed since we met last time. 我们上次相见至今已经三年了。 3. Fifteen minutes elapsed before the performance began. 过了15分钟演出才开始。 4. They met again after an elapse of many years. 他们多年后又相逢。', '过去式: elapsed 过去分词: elapsed 现在分词: elapsing 第三人称单数: elapses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('watch', '[wɑːtʃ]', 'v.注视；看守；观看 n.手表；监视；看守；值班', '1. I seldom play chess, but I like to watch. 我很少下棋，但是喜欢看。 2. Watch what I do and how I do it. 注意看我的动作和方法。 3. I was assigned to watch the road. 我被派去护路。 4. We sat there watching basketball. 我们坐在那看篮球比赛。 5. How much is that watch? 那块手表多少钱?', '过去式: watched 过去分词: watched 现在分词: watching 第三人称单数: watches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enforce', '[ɪn\'fɔːrs]', 'vt.强迫；强制；实施；执行；加强', '1. You can\'t enforce cooperation between the players. 队员间的配合并非强迫命令而成。 2. Don\'t enforce your will on the child, please. 请别把你的意愿强加给这孩子。 3. Contracts are promises that the law will enforce. 合同是可强制执行的一项或一组诺言。 4. It may be possible to enforce part of a contract. 合同可以部分被强制执行。', '形容词: enforceable 名词: enforceability 过去式: enforced 过去分词: enforced 现在分词: enforcing 第三人称单数: enforces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sack', '[sæk]', 'n.袋子；解雇 vt.解雇；把 ... 装入袋子；劫掠', '1. There is a sack of potatoes in the corner of the room. 屋子一角有一袋马铃薯。 2. He tumbled his clothes and books into a big sack. 他把他的衣服和书胡乱装进一只大口袋。 3. The poor guy got the sack yesterday. 那个可怜的家伙昨天给辞退了。 4. If you are late again, the boss will sack you. 如果你再迟到,老板就会解雇你。', '过去式: sacked 过去分词: sacked 现在分词: sacking 第三人称单数: sacks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spider', '[\'spaɪdər]', 'n.蜘蛛；十字叉；三脚架；长柄平底锅', '1. The spider can catch insects by cobweb. 蜘蛛能用蜘蛛网抓住昆虫。 2. The little girl thinks spiders are terrible creatures. 小女孩认为蜘蛛是一种可怕的生物。 3. The main components of a spider cardan joint include the spider, yokes and quill bearings, etc. 其主要部件包括十字轴、万向节叉以及滚针轴承等。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('odd', '[ɑːd]', 'adj.奇数的；古怪的；零散的；剩余的', '1. 1,3, 5 and 7 are odd numbers. 1,3, 5 和 7 是奇数。 2. Graphs are on even pages and tables are on odd pages. 图在偶数页,表格在奇数页。 3. It\'s very odd that she didn\'t reply to our letter. 她没有回我们的信是件很奇怪的事。 4. On the way, one can watch pines in all kinds of odd shapes. 一路上,人们可以观赏到各种各样形态怪异的松树。', '副词: oddly 比较级: odder 最高级: oddest 名词: oddness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stroke', '[stroʊk]', 'n.中风；击打；一笔（画）；意外的运气 v.击打 v.轻抚；奉承', '1. I know a doctor. He is expert in curing stroke. 我认识一个医生,专治中风。 2. He fell the tree with one stroke of the axe. 他一斧头就将树砍倒。 3. It\'s easy to draw a snake. Just one stroke. 画蛇不难,一笔就可以完成拉。 4. It was a stroke of luck that I found you here. 我在这里碰见你真是运气。 5. She stroked the ball cleverly past her opponent. 她巧妙地一击把球打过对手。 6. The cat likes being stroked. 猫喜欢让人抚摸。', '名词: stroker 过去式: stroked 过去分词: stroked 现在分词: stroking 第三人称单数: strokes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('throughout', '[θruː\'aʊt]', 'prep.遍及；贯穿 adv.自始至终；到处', '1. The disease spread throughout the country. 这种疾病蔓延全国。 2. She remained cheerful throughout the trip. 旅行中她始终兴致勃勃。 3. It snowed throughout the night. 雪整整下了一夜。 4. Throughout history empires have waxed and waned. 历史上各个帝国革故鼎新均有兴衰。 5. The prince remained loyal throughout. 王子自始至终忠贞不渝。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heave', '[hiːv]', 'v.用力举起；抛出；扔；恶心；（费力地）发出（叹息等） n.举；抛；起伏', '1. They heave at the heavy box, but can not lift it. 他们想搬动那只很重的箱子，但抬不起来。 2. He hove a chair through the window. 他把椅子从窗户中抛出。 3. Heave the rocks into the ravine. 把这些石头扔进深谷里。 4. It\'s a very bad thing to heave things around. 把东西到处乱扔是很不好的习惯。 5. With one more heave, we got the box onto the shelf. 我们再使把劲,就把箱子抬到架子上了。', '名词: heaver 过去式: heaved 过去分词: heaved 现在分词: heaving 第三人称单数: heaves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clasp', '[klæsp]', 'n.扣子；钩；紧握；握手 v.扣紧；紧握；密切合作', '1. The button won\'t clasp. 扣子扣不上。', '过去式: clasped 过去分词: clasped 现在分词: clasping 第三人称单数: clasps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pad', '[pæd]', 'n.便签纸；衬垫；发射台；公寓；脚印；肉趾 n.低沉声音；缓慢行走的马 v.填塞；夸大 v.轻轻走', '1. She always kept a pad and pencil by the phone. 她总在电话机旁准备一本便签簿和一支铅笔。 2. He jotted down a note on the pad by the telephone. 他在电话机旁的便笺本草草记下一个通知。 3. That carpet needs a pad under it. 那块地毯下面要铺衬垫。 4. The nurse put a clean pad of cotton over his wound. 护士在他的伤口上敷了一块干净的纱布垫。 5. She heard the pad of bare feet coming down the stairs. 她听见有光着脚下楼的轻柔声音。 6. The helmet is padded with foam. 头盔以泡沫材料填充。 7. They like to pad along this lane. 他们喜欢慢慢地走。', '形容词: padless 名词: padder 过去式: padded 过去分词: padded 现在分词: padding 第三人称单数: pads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('indicative', '[ɪn\'dɪkətɪv]', 'adj.指示的；暗示的；【语】陈述的 n.陈述语气', '1. Use the indicative mood to make a sentence. 请用陈述语气造句。 2. There are three moods, indicative, imperative and subjunctive in English. 英语中有三种语气，即陈述语气，祈使语气和虚拟语气。', '副词: indicatively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('one', '[wʌn]', 'n.一；一个；一体 adj.一个的；某一个的；唯一的；同一的 pron.任何人；某人', '1. A person has one head and one neck. 每人都有一个头，一个脖子。 2. No one can live without breathing. 没有一个人可以不呼吸而生存。 3. If only problems would come one at a time! 要是问题一次只发生一个该多好！ 4. One should do his best for the cause of world peace. 一个人应该为世界和平事业尽最大努力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('roast', '[roʊst]', 'n.烤肉；烘烤 v.烤；烘焙；晒；<俚>痛斥 adj.烘烤的；烤过的', '1. Let\'s have a nice roast for Sunday dinner. 我们星期天晚上好好吃一顿烤肉吧。 2. His mouth watered at the sight of roast. 他看见烤肉就垂涎三尺。 3. They had a hot dog roast last Sunday. 他们上星期天举行了一次烤热狗野餐会。 4. The beef is roasting nicely on the spit. 这块牛肉在烤肉叉上烤得很好。 5. His favorite dish is roast duck. 他最喜欢吃的菜是烤鸭。', '过去式: roasted 过去分词: roasted 现在分词: roasting 第三人称单数: roasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comb', '[koʊm]', 'n.梳子；鸡冠；蜂房 v.梳理；彻底搜寻', '1. She wore a small comb as an ornament. 她佩戴了一把小梳子作为装饰品。 2. She swept her hair back with a comb. 她用梳子将头发往后梳。 3. Morris said taco sauce makes her comb light up bright red. 莫里斯说，吃蘸酱墨西哥煎玉米卷让小鸡的鸡冠变得油亮鲜红。 4. His comb was as red as fire, and his feathers were as yellow as gold. 他的鸡冠鲜红似火，羽毛橙黄如金。 5. She combed the mud out of the dog\'s fur. 她梳去狗的皮毛中的泥土。', '过去式: combed 过去分词: combed 现在分词: combing 第三人称单数: combs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('leather', '[\'leðər]', 'n.皮革；皮制品 adj.皮革制的 vt.用皮鞭抽打；用皮革覆盖', '1. This wallet feels to me like leather. 我觉得这钱包像是皮的。 2. Leather can deteriorate in damp conditions. 皮革受潮可变质。 3. Plastic is sometimes used instead of leather. 塑胶有时可以替代皮革。 4. Our factory\'s leather products show genuine leather in its natural colors. 本厂皮制品，还我真皮本色。 5. I have a pair of leather mittens. 我有一副皮连指手套。 6. I\'d like to leather him black and blue. 我要把他揍得青一块紫一块的。', '过去式: leathered 过去分词: leathered 现在分词: leathering 第三人称单数: leathers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('everybody', '[\'evribɑːdi]', 'pron.每人；人人；各人', '1. Everybody should do good self work. 每人必须做好自己的工作。 2. It is difficult to find a time that suits everybody. 很难找到一个对每人都合适的时间。 3. The rascal was hated by everybody in the village. 这坏蛋，村子里人人痛恨。 4. Everybody else has gone home except me. 除我之外，人人都回家了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('account', '[ə\'kaʊnt]', 'n.账户；帐目；赊账；老主顾；报告；描述；解释；说明；估计；理由；利益；好处；根据 v.解释；导致；报账；把 ... 视为；归咎(于)', '1. She squared her account at the store. 她在商店里结清帐目。 2. We have accounts with most of our suppliers. 我们与大多数供应商都是实行赊购制。 3. The agency has lost several of its most important accounts. 这家代理机构失去了几家最重要的老客户。 4. This is a particular account of the accident. 这是一份全面而详尽的事故报告。 5. He has been asked to account for his conduct. 他被要求解释他的行为。', '过去式: accounted 过去分词: accounted 现在分词: accounting 第三人称单数: accounts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('graduate', '[\'ɡrædʒuət]', 'n.毕业生 vt.毕业；标以刻度；定等级 vi.毕业；获学位；逐渐变得 adj.毕业的；获得学位的', '1. He is a graduate in medicine. 他是医科毕业生。 2. He is a graduate of Tokyo University. 他是东京大学的毕业生。 3. They graduate 30,000 engineers every year. 每年有3万名工程师从学校毕业。 4. This ruler is graduated in centimeters. 这把尺的刻度是厘米。 5. He will graduate from the school in May. 他将要在五月份毕业。 6. She was taken on as a graduate trainee. 她应聘为新毕业的实习生。', '名词: graduator 过去式: graduated 过去分词: graduated 现在分词: graduating 第三人称单数: graduates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('marry', '[\'mæri]', 'v.娶；结婚；嫁；结合', '1. He will marry the girl first or last. 他迟早会娶那姑娘的。 2. My hope is that I can marry her. 我的希望是能娶她。 3. Much as I like her, I will not marry her. 我虽然很喜欢她，却不打算娶她。 4. Will you marry me? 你愿意和我结婚吗？', '过去式: married 过去分词: married 现在分词: marrying 第三人称单数: marries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ambiguous', '[æm\'bɪɡjuəs]', 'adj.模棱两可的；含糊不清的', '1. He gave us an ambiguous answer . 他给了我们一个模棱两可的答复。 2. In fact, your ambiguous words amount to a refusal. 实际上,你说的那些模棱两可的话等于是拒绝。 3. Her account was deliberately ambiguous. 她的陈述故意含混不清。 4. Why are you always so ambiguous about this problem? 为什么你总是对这个问题含糊不清？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('envy', '[\'envi]', 'v.羡慕；妒忌 n.羡慕；(妒忌的)对象', '1. They envy him his good fortune. 他们羡慕他的好运气。 2. I envy her ability to dance in front of a crowd. 她在众人面前所展现的的舞技令我羡慕不已。 3. Don\'t envy anyone who lives better than you. 不要妒忌比你日子过得好的任何人。 4. He was filled with envy at my success. 他对我的成功满怀羡慕。', '副词: envyingly 名词: envier 名词复数: envies 过去式: envied 过去分词: envied 现在分词: envying 第三人称单数: envies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('car', '[kɑːr]', 'n.汽车；车厢；吊舱', '1. A new type of car is on the market now. 现在一种新型小汽车正在上市。 2. Repairing your car will cost a minimum of 100 dollars. 修理你的汽车最低限度要100美元。 3. The car in front of me stopped suddenly and I had to brake. 我前面那辆小汽车突然停住，我只好刹车。 4. This car has just been cut out from the train. 这节车厢刚从列车脱下。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('erect', '[ɪ\'rekt]', 'vt.使竖立；建立；建造 adj.直立的；竖立的；笔直的', '1. They erected their tent at the foot of the mountain. 他们在山脚下支起了帐篷。 2. The town will erect a monument to its war heroes . 这个市镇将为该城的战斗英雄们立个纪念碑。 3. Six policemen started to erect a roadblock. 六个警察着手建立一道路障。 4. They plan to erect an apartment house on that property. 他们计划在那片地产上建造一座公寓楼。 5. She held her head erect and her back straight. 她昂着头，把背挺得笔直。', '形容词: erectable 副词: erectly 名词: erectness 过去式: erected 过去分词: erected 现在分词: erecting 第三人称单数: erects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('knot', '[nɑːt]', 'n.结；节 vi.打结 vt.把 ... 打成结；系牢；捆扎', '1. This knot keeps loosening. 这个结老松开。 2. My dead fingers could not untie the knot. 我的手指麻木了，解不开结。 3. The knot was fastened in such a way that it was impossible to undo. 这个结系得那么紧,根本解不开。 4. It was just a big knot up on the branch. 那只是树枝上的一个节瘤。 5. This wire is too stiff to knot easily. 这线太硬不容易打结。 6. Loop that end of the rope through this and knot it. 把绳子的这一头儿从这里穿过然后打结。', '过去式: knotted 过去分词: knotted 现在分词: knotting 第三人称单数: knots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sit', '[sɪt]', 'v.坐；栖息；使就座 n.坐；栖息', '1. He sat at his desk working. 他坐在桌子旁边工作。 2. The students sit in a circle on the floor. 学生们在地板上坐成一圈。 3. There is a sparrow sitting on a branch. 有只麻雀栖在树枝上。 4. Sit yourself down and tell us what happened. 你坐下，告诉我们怎么回事。 5. Would you like a sit on the deck-chair? 在躺椅上坐一会儿好吗？', '过去式: sat 过去分词: sat 现在分词: sitting 第三人称单数: sits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('in', '[ɪn]', 'prep.在 ... 里；在 ... 地方；在 ... 期间；在 ... 方面；进入...里面；处于...状态；穿着...；以...的方式 adv.在家；入；进；向里；在某地；并入；在某种关系中 adj.在里面的；新来的；执政的；<口>时髦的 n.当权者；影响；达成目标的路径', '1. The telephone was in the little study on the ground floor. 电话在底楼的小书房里。 2. The books are printed in Hong Kong. 这些书在香港印刷。 3. They are in research of this new technique. 他们正在研究这种新工艺。 4. He is a layman in economics. 他对经济学一窍不通。 5. He is not in at the moment. 这个时候他不在家。 6. The in part of the machine is very complex. 该机器内部结构非常复杂。 7. The election made him an in. 这次选举使他成为执政者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prosperity', '[prɑː\'sperəti]', 'n.繁荣；兴旺', '1. The new government ushered in a period of prosperity. 新政府的成立带来了一个繁荣的时期。 2. The empire was on the wane after its period of prosperity. 帝国经过全盛以后逐渐衰落。 3. We hope to have a life of happiness and prosperity. 我们希望拥有成功幸福的生活。 4. Prosperity destroys fools and endangers the wise. 繁荣兴旺既毁了蠢人，也使智者陷于险境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('barrel', '[\'bærəl]', 'n.桶；枪管；一桶的量；炮管；大量；笔管；汽油桶 vi.快速移动 vt.把 ... 装桶', '1. Beer swilled around the bottom of the barrel. 啤酒在桶底晃荡。 2. The beer comes out of the barrel under pressure. 啤酒受到压力从桶中流出。 3. This barrel contains 50 litres. 这个桶容量为50升。 4. He made a barrel with staves by himself. 他自己用桶板做了一只桶。 5. They planned to barrel the beer next Monday. 他们打算下星期一把啤酒装桶。', '过去式: barreled/barrelled 过去分词: barreled/barrelled 现在分词: barreling/barrelling 第三人称单数: barrels/barrels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dash', '[dæʃ]', 'v.猛冲；猛掷；泼溅；匆忙完成 n.破折号；短跑；猛冲；冲', '1. He dashed across the street and ran towards me. 他冲过马路，向我跑过来。 2. He dash the glass bowl to bit on a rock. 他对著石块把玻璃碗砸得粉碎。 3. Don\'t dash the paint on the wall like that. 别那样在墙上乱涂漆。 4. She dashed off a letter to her mother. 她给母亲匆匆写了一封信。 5. The dash is used in writing to show a pause. 在写作上破折号用来表示停顿。', '过去式: dashed 过去分词: dashed 现在分词: dashing 第三人称单数: dashes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shallow', '[\'ʃæloʊ]', 'adj.浅的；薄的 n.浅滩；浅处 v.变浅', '1. This shallow ford made it possible for us to cross the river. 我们有可能从这片浅滩过河。 2. That dish is too shallow to serve soup in. 那只盘子太浅了，不能盛汤。 3. Homesickness is a shallow strait, I stand here, my homeland is on the other side. 乡愁是一湾浅浅的海峡,我在这头,大陆在那头。 4. She has a rather shallow personality. 她的个性相当浅薄。 5. This shallow ford made it possible for us to cross the river. 我们有可能从这片浅滩过河。 6. The rock assemblage of shallow exposed bank-microfacies is the basis of the formation of pore layers and reservoir permeability systems. 变浅暴露滩微相的岩石组合是孔隙层和储渗体形成的基础。', '副词: shallowly 比较级: shallower 最高级: shallowest 名词: shallowness 过去式: shallowed 过去分词: shallowed 现在分词: shallowing 第三人称单数: shallows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blood', '[blʌd]', 'n.血；血统；仇恨 vt.流血', '1. The dog\'s fur was matted with blood. 那只狗的毛皮上沾有血迹。 2. She was sick at the sight of the blood. 她一见到血就感到恶心。 3. A drop of blood slid down his leg. 他的腿上流着一点儿血。 4. The wounded man was covered with blood. 这个受伤的人身上全是血。 5. He did not want to see any American blood spilt. 他不想看到任何美国人流血牺牲。', '过去式: blooded 过去分词: blooded 现在分词: blooding 第三人称单数: bloods');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('writing', '[\'raɪtɪŋ]', 'n.写作；著述；笔迹；作品', '1. Writing is his life. 写作是他的生命。 2. She is endowed with great writing ability. 她具有杰出的写作天赋。 3. She doesn\'t earn much from her writing. 她写作得到的收入不多。 4. The ones that described the victor of this war and loser had a lot of writing. 描写这场战争的胜利者和失败者的著述也很多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('screw', '[skruː]', 'n.螺钉；螺丝；螺状物；螺旋桨；螺旋；吝啬鬼；监狱看守人；<粗>性交；<英俚>工资；薪水 v.拧紧；拧；压榨；<粗>性交', '1. Turn the screw to the right to tighten it. 将螺钉向右旋紧。 2. One of the screws is loose. 一只螺丝松了。 3. The screw did its work, and Ressel was pleased. 由于螺旋桨起了作用，所以莱塞尔感到高兴。 4. He used all of his efforts to loosen the screw. 他用尽全力来拧开这个螺旋装置。 5. The table legs are screwed to the floor. 这张桌子的腿是用螺丝固定在地板上的。', '形容词: screwable 名词: screwer 过去式: screwed 过去分词: screwed 现在分词: screwing 第三人称单数: screws');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('confine', '[kən\'faɪn]', 'vt.限制；禁闭 n.范围；界限；约束；限制', '1. I wish the speaker would confine himself to the subject. 我希望演说者不要离题。 2. I am sick, I have to confine to bed. 我病了，我得卧床休息。 3. The thief was confined in a prison. 窃贼被关押在监狱里。 4. Is it cruel to confine a bird in a cage? 把鸟关在笼子里残忍不残忍? 5. This is outside the confines of human knowledge. 这超出了人类知识范畴。', '形容词: confinable 名词: confiner 过去式: confined 过去分词: confined 现在分词: confining 第三人称单数: confines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('maiden', '[\'meɪdn]', 'n.未婚女子；少女；断头机；从未赢过的赛马 adj.未婚的；处女的；初次的', '1. The old song was about a fair maiden and her suitors. 这个旧歌唱的是一个漂亮的未婚女人和她的求婚者的事。 2. The prince fell in love with a fair young maiden. 王子爱上了一位美丽的年轻少女。 3. The poem is about a fair maiden. 这首诗描述的是一个美丽的少女。 4. What\'s your mother\'s maiden name? 你母亲结婚前的姓名?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tender', '[\'tendər]', 'adj.温柔的；脆弱的；敏感的；亲切的；嫩的；痛的 v.提出；投标 n.投标；照管人；补给船；煤水车', '1. She is always tender and soft-spoken. 她总是那么温柔,轻声细语。 2. He gave her a tender kiss. 他给了她一个温柔的吻。 3. Love is a river that drowns the tender reed. 爱情是条会淹没柔弱芦苇的河流。 4. Don\'t mention his divorce---it\'s a very tender subject. 别提他离婚的事---那是个敏感话题。 5. I\'ll tender my resignation. 我要提出辞职。 6. His tender for building a mansion has been accepted. 他承办大厦筑的投标被接受了。', '副词: tenderly 比较级: tenderer 最高级: tenderest 名词: tenderness 过去式: tendered 过去分词: tendered 现在分词: tendering 第三人称单数: tenders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sew', '[soʊ]', 'v.缝合；缝纫', '1. The skirt is finished I\'m now going to sew a pocket on. 裙子做好了--我现在再缝上个口袋。 2. I\'ll just sew up that tear, and the coat will be as good as new. 我把大衣的破处缝好，就会完好如新了。 3. Sew that part all along. 把那部分从头到尾缝合起来。 4. Tack the folds down before you sew them firmly into place. 先用大针脚将褶子松松地缀住，然后再将其缝纫到位。', '形容词: sewable 过去式: sewed 过去分词: sewn/sewed 现在分词: sewing 第三人称单数: sews');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('order', '[\'ɔːrdər]', 'n.顺序；条理；订单；命令；秩序；阶层；[生]目；点的东西 v.命令；定购；调整；整理；点餐；预定，订货', '1. Today we\'ll reverse the usual order of the lesson. 今天我们将把通常的上课顺序倒过来。 2. The house had been kept in good order. 房子保持得井井有条。 3. An extraordinarily large order bucked up all the staff. 一份特大订单使全体员工欢欣鼓舞。 4. The order urged the armed forces to enhance their alertness. 该项命令敦促武装部队提高警惕。 5. The commander ordered a counterattack. 司令官命令反攻。', '名词: orderer 过去式: ordered 过去分词: ordered 现在分词: ordering 第三人称单数: orders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('allocate', '[\'æləkeɪt]', 'vt.分派；分配；分配额', '1. The system was unable to allocate a new data object. 系统无法分派新的数据对象。 2. Allocate rations for a week - long campingtrip. 分配一星期外出野营的定额。 3. You must allocate the money carefully. 你们必须谨慎地分配钱。', '形容词: allocable 名词: allocation 过去式: allocated 过去分词: allocated 现在分词: allocating 第三人称单数: allocates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('new', '[nuː]', 'adj.新的；崭新的；新鲜的；不熟悉的 adv.新近地', '1. I\'ll just sew up that tear, and the coat will be as good as new. 我把大衣的破处缝好，就会完好如新了。 2. They sell new and used furniture. 他们出售新旧家具。 3. The book seemed to open up before me a new world. 那本书好象在我面前揭示出一个崭新的世界。 4. There is nothing new under the sun. 太阳底下没有新鲜的事。', '比较级: newer 最高级: newest 名词: newness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gene', '[dʒiːn]', 'n.基因', '1. The position that a given gene occupies on a chromosome. 基因座在一条染色体上某种给定基因所占的位置 2. The degree to which an expressed gene produces its effects in an organism. 基因的表现度描述一个组织中的一个基因产生作用的程度 3. In addition to gene, intelligence also depends on an adequate diet, a good education and a decent home environment. 除了遗传基因外，智力的高低还取决于良好的营养，良好的教育和良好的家庭环境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relation', '[rɪ\'leɪʃn]', 'n.关系；联系；亲戚；陈述；参考', '1. Relation between the two countries has reached a crisis point. 两国关系已达到出现危机的地步。 2. We try to maintain good relation with our customer. 我们努力与客户保持良好的关系。 3. We wish to establish relation with you. 我们希望与你们建立贸易关系。 4. I don\'t see any relation between the two problems. 我看不出这两个问题间的联系。', '名词复数: relations');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('liver', '[\'lɪvər]', 'n.肝脏', '1. The poor man has a serious disease of the liver. 这个可怜的人患有严重的肝病。 2. He\'s got a cancer in his liver. 他得了肝癌。 3. Excessive dosage of this drug can result in injury to the liver. 这种药使用过量会损害肝脏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('linger', '[\'lɪŋɡər]', 'vi.徘徊；逗留；消磨；漫步', '1. The beautiful melody is lingering in my mind. 美妙的音乐在我心中回荡。 2. She linger after the concert, hoping to meet the star. 音乐会后她徘徊不去，希望能遇见明星。 3. He made excuses to linger on the stairs. 他找借口故意在楼梯口上磨磨蹭蹭。 4. We can\'t linger any more, because we have so many works unfinished. 我们有这么作业还没完成,不能在拖延了。', '副词: lingeringly 名词: lingerer 过去式: lingered 过去分词: lingered 现在分词: lingering 第三人称单数: lingers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thick', '[θɪk]', 'adj.厚的；浓密的；粗的；愚笨的', '1. He put on a thick sweater since it was cold in the morning. 早晨很冷，他穿上了一件厚毛衣。 2. The mountain was covered with a thick layer of snow. 山上覆盖了一层厚厚的白雪。 3. There is a thick forest behind the village. 村子后面有一片密密的森林。 4. Her thick and dark hair hangs all the way to her shoulder. 她那又粗又黑的头发一直披到肩。', '形容词: thickish 副词: thickly 比较级: thicker 最高级: thickest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scarf', '[skɑːrf]', 'n.围巾', '1. The price of this scarf is below ten dollars. 这条围巾价格不到10美元。 2. She twisted the long scarf round her head. 她把那条长围巾围在头上。 3. She threw a scarf over her shoulders. 她在肩上披上一块肩巾。', '名词: scarfer 名词复数: scarves 过去式: scarfed 过去分词: scarfed 现在分词: scarfing 第三人称单数: scarfs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('subsequent', '[\'sʌbsɪkwənt]', 'adj.随后的；后来的', '1. Subsequent events proved me wrong. 後来发生的事证明我错了。 2. He confessed to other crimes subsequent to the bank robbery. 他供认抢劫银行案後，又坦白了其他罪行。 3. Subsequent to its success as a play, it was made into a film. 该剧在舞台上获得成功之後，又摄制成了电影。 4. Subsequent events confirmed our doubts. 后来发生的事证实了我们的怀疑。', '副词: subsequently 名词: subsequence');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nearby', '[ˌnɪr\'baɪ]', 'adj.附近的 adv.在附近', '1. He usually trades at the nearby supermarket. 他通常在附近的超市购物。 2. He roped his horse on a nearby tree. 他把马拴到附近的一棵树上。 3. I can hear the hymn from the nearby church. 我能听到从附近的教堂传来的圣歌。 4. The whole village is up in arms about the proposal to build an airport nearby. 全村强烈反对在附近修建机场的计划。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deem', '[diːm]', 'v.认为；视作', '1. They were deemed to be illegal immigrants. 他们被认为是不法移民。 2. They deemed that he was no longer capable of managing the business. 他们认为他没有能力再继续管理这个公司了。 3. These buildings are deemed to be of architectural importance and must be protected. 这些楼房被视为具有建筑的重要性', '过去式: deemed 过去分词: deemed 现在分词: deeming 第三人称单数: deems');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('vocation', '[voʊ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.职业；行业；使命', '1. She chose nursing as her vocation. 她选择护士为职业。 2. He was equipped with knowledge for the vocation. 他具有这项职业的学识。 3. She struggled for years to find her true vocation. 她多年来苦苦寻找真正适合自己的职业。 4. The industry is facing vocation conformity in China. 在中国,这种工业面临行业整合。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pollution', '[pə\'luːʃn]', 'n.污染；污染物', '1. They devised proposals to deal with air pollution. 他们构想出处理空气污染的方案。 2. Waste water from the factory is the main cause of the pollution of local rivers. 来自那家工厂的污水是当地河流污染的主要原因。 3. Many young people could not resist the spiritual pollution. 很多年轻人不能抵制精神污染。 4. The main pollution sources include: slag, sewage water, smoke, and tail gas. 主要污染物有矿渣，污水，烟气、尾气等。', '动词: pollute');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mathematical', '[ˌmæθə\'mætɪkl]', 'adj.数学的；精确的；可能性极小的', '1. He\'s deeply engrossed in mathematical research. 他醉心于数学的研究。 2. It is important not to be overawed by the mathematical jargon. 要紧的是不要被数学的术语所吓倒。 3. Both rely on mathematical calculations to determine the location from which a positron or photon was emitted. 这两种成像方法均依靠精确的计算来决定正电子或光于发射的位置。 4. The accurate mathematical model of WIM is difficult to establish because WIM\'s parameters change with time when they work. 摘要动态称重系统在测量的过程中为一时变系统，难以对称重系统建立精确的数学模型。', '副词: mathematically 异体字: mathematic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jazz', '[dʒæz]', 'n.爵士乐；<俚>空话；各种杂物 vt.使有生气；以爵士风格演奏 vi.跳爵士舞；奏爵士乐；游荡', '1. She\'s potty about jazz. 她迷上了爵士音乐。 2. I don\'t dig modern jazz. 我不喜欢现代爵士乐。 3. Does jazz hold any appeal for you? 你对爵士乐有兴趣吗？ 4. Jazz has never really turned me on. 我从未对爵士乐真正产生过兴趣。 5. We need to jazz this room up a bit. 我们需要把这间屋子装饰一下使之更有生气。 6. I don\'t like to jazz up the classics. 我不喜欢用爵士乐的形式来演奏古典乐曲。', '形容词: jazzish 名词: jazzer 过去式: jazzed 过去分词: jazzed 现在分词: jazzing 第三人称单数: jazzes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('turkey', '[\'tɜːrki]', 'n.火鸡；笨蛋；失败之作 n.[T-]土耳其', '1. It\'s traditional in England to eat turkey on Christmas Day. 圣诞节时吃火鸡是英格兰的传统。 2. People often drink white wine with turkey. 人们经常边吃火鸡肉边喝白葡萄酒。 3. Russia thereupon declared war upon Turkey. 俄国于是对土耳其宣战。', '名词复数: turkeys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('offset', '[\'ɔːfset]', 'vt.抵消；弥补；用平版印刷 vi.形成分支 n.补偿；平版印刷；支派；弯管；[计]偏移量', '1. The pay raise will be offset by inflation. 增加的工资会被通货膨胀所抵销。 2. Higher mortgage rates are partly offset by increased tax allowances. 抵押款提高了，其中一部分可由免税额增加而抵消。 3. Hedge can help them offset inventory loss when commodity price fall. 在商品价格下跌时,套期保值能够帮助他们抵补存货价跌的损失。 4. He raised his prices to offset the increased cost of materials. 他提高售价以补偿材料增加的成本。 5. Offset requirements also vary between these areas. 补偿要求在这些地区也各有不同。', '过去式: offset 过去分词: offset 现在分词: offsetting 第三人称单数: offsets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('steer', '[stɪr]', 'v.操纵；驾驶；掌舵；引导', '1. Sometimes an oar is used to steer a boat. 有时桨用以操纵小舟。 2. He steered the car skillfully through the narrow streets. 他熟练地驾驶着汽车穿过狭窄的街道。 3. People used to steer by the stars. 过去人们常常参照星星的方位来驾驶。 4. The old man settled himself to steer. 老人坐定下来掌舵。', '形容词: steerable 名词: steerer 过去式: steered 过去分词: steered 现在分词: steering 第三人称单数: steers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('warn', '[wɔːrn]', 'vt.警告；告诫；预先通知 vi.发出警告', '1. He warned me against going there at night. 他警告我晚上不要到那去。 2. They warn her that if she do it again she will be sent to prison. 他们警告她说她再这么干就把她关进监狱。 3. The police warn us not to go out at night. 警察告诫我们夜间不要出门。 4. I warned them that there might be snakes in the woods. 我提醒他们树林里可能有蛇。 5. Birds sometimes chatter to each other to warn of danger. 鸟儿有时互相啁啾,通报危险。', '名词: warner 过去式: warned 过去分词: warned 现在分词: warning 第三人称单数: warns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mobilize', '[\'moʊbəlaɪz]', 'vt.动员；调动；使移动；使流通 vi.动员起来', '1. They are mobilizing their supporters to vote at the election. 他们正在组织其支持者向他们拉选票。 2. Our country\'s in great danger; we must mobilize the army. 我们正处于严重危险之中，我们必须把军人动员起来。 3. The President had constitutional power to mobilize troops in an emergency. 依据宪法，总统有权在紧急情况下调动军队。 4. The troops received orders to mobilize. 部队接到动员令。', '名词: mobilization 过去式: mobilized 过去分词: mobilized 现在分词: mobilizing 第三人称单数: mobilizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('minor', '[\'maɪnər]', 'adj.轻微的；较小的；次要的 n.未成年人；辅修科目；[音]小调 v.辅修', '1. You should be thankful that you have escaped with only minor injuries. 你应该感到庆幸,你只是受了点轻伤,但是却脱险了。 2. We can only make minor concessions, but it might break the deadlock. 我们只能做些较小的让步，但这就可能打破僵局。 3. She played a minor role in the movie. 她在电影中扮演了一个次要的角色。 4. It is illegal to sell cigarettes to minors. 向未成年人出售香烟是违法的。 5. Many university students will minor in some practical courses. 许多大学生都会副修一些实用性的课程。', '过去式: minored 过去分词: minored 现在分词: minoring 第三人称单数: minors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sport', '[spɔːrt]', 'n.运动；体育 vi.嬉戏；炫耀；戏弄 adj.运动的；户外穿戴的', '1. Baseball is more popular than any other sport in Japan. 在日本，棒球比其他任何运动都受人欢迎。 2. Football is my favorite sport. 足球是我最喜欢的运动。 3. Sport is being debased by commercialism. 体育运动的价值受商业化的影响而逐渐下降。 4. This sport event attracted many advertisers. 这个体育项目吸引了许多广告客户。 5. Don\'t sport with her， she\'s an old-fashioned girl. 别跟她开玩笑,她是个古板的姑娘。 6. Jump into the extreme sport of Skydiving. 跳转到极限运动的跳伞运动。', '形容词: sportful 副词: sportfully 名词: sportfulness 过去式: sported 过去分词: sported 现在分词: sporting 第三人称单数: sports');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blank', '[blæŋk]', 'adj.空白的；茫然的 n.[C]空白；空白处', '1. Give me a blank sheet of paper, please. 请给我一张空白的纸。 2. Many blank spaces are still left in the suburbs. 郊区仍留有许多空地。 3. Her explanations were met with blank incomprehension. 大家对她的解释茫然不解。 4. His expression remained studiously blank. 他的表情仍是那种故作茫然状。 5. My life before that is a blank to me. 那以前的生活对我来说已是一片空白。', '副词: blankly 比较级: blanker 最高级: blankest 名词: blankness 过去式: blanked 过去分词: blanked 现在分词: blanking 第三人称单数: blanks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conquest', '[\'kɑːŋkwest]', 'n.征服；占领地；战利品；俘虏', '1. They succeeded in the conquest of the city. 他们成功地征服了这座城市。 2. The Normans ruled England by right of conquest. 诺曼人征服了英格兰成了统治者。 3. The conquest of this rare disease has always been her aim. 征服这种罕见的疾病一直是她奋斗的目标。 4. The Romans extended their conquests to Britain. 罗马人把征服范围扩大到了不列颠。', '名词复数: conquests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surface', '[\'sɜːrfɪs]', 'n.表面；外表；平面 adj.表面的；肤浅的 vt.在 ... 上加表层；使 ... 成平面 vi.浮到水面；显露；在表面工作', '1. The scheme seems on the surface to be quite practical. 这方案表面上看来似乎很实际。 2. A wave broke across the surface of the pool. 一个波浪从池水表面掠过。 3. Beneath that apparently calm surface is a man of fierce temper. 文静的外表掩盖着的是一个火暴脾气的人。 4. The surface of the lake is quite still. 湖面相当平静。 5. This essay is so short that it can only scratch the surface of the topic. 这篇文章很短，只能对这一问题作肤浅的探讨。 6. We are going to surface this road. 我们将要为这条路铺路面。 7. Fish were surfacing to catch insects. 鱼浮到水面上捕捉昆虫。', '过去式: surfaced 过去分词: surfaced 现在分词: surfacing 第三人称单数: surfaces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('controversy', '[\'kɒntrəˌvɜːsɪ]', 'n.争议；(公开的)争论', '1. The mayor will try to accord the controversy over the housing scheme. 市长试图调解住房规划方面的争议。 2. The remark touched off a heated controversy. 这句话引起了热烈的争论。 3. The new government appointments have caused much controversy. 政府在人事上作的新的委任，引起了许多争论。', '名词复数: controversies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appearance', '[ə\'pɪrəns]', 'n.出现；露面；外貌；外表；出场', '1. The journal makes its appearance once two months. 这本刊物两个月出版一次。 2. The appearance of Internet marked the beginning of the age of information. 因特网的出现标志着信息时代的开始。 3. I don\'t want to go to the party but I\'d better put in an appearance, I suppose. 我不想参加那个聚会，可是我最好还是要露一下面。 4. We should not judge a person by his appearance. 我们不应该以貌取人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('monitor', '[\'mɑːnɪtər]', 'v.监视；监督；监听 n.班长；监视器；监听员；[计算机]显示器', '1. Police officers have been closely monitoring the organization\'s activities. 警方密切地监视着该组织的活动。 2. He will monitor and review the company\'s rules and regulations. 他将监督并审查该公司的规章制度。 3. This instrument monitors the patient\'s heartbeats. 这台仪器监听病人的心跳。 4. The monitor handed the papers out to the classmates. 班长把试卷分发给同学们。', '名词: monitorship 过去式: monitored 过去分词: monitored 现在分词: monitoring 第三人称单数: monitors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('density', '[\'densəti]', 'n.密度；浓度；比重', '1. Mercury has a much greater density than water. 水银的密度比水大得多。 2. The density of population in this city is very high. 这个城市的人口密度非常高。 3. The driver had to stop because the density of the fog made it difficult to see. 由於浓雾使道路很难看清,司机不得不停车。 4. The next trail would require a slightly higher filling density acid. 在下一次试验时需要注入比重较高的酸。', '名词复数: densities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lodge', '[lɑːdʒ]', 'n.小屋；巢穴；门房；传达室；支部 v.存放；临时住宿；安顿；提出(报告、抗议等)', '1. We drove to our lodge on the lake for the summer. 我们驱车来到湖滨小屋度夏。 2. Yet the beaver lodge remained sturdy and strong. 然而，海狸的巢穴却依然强韧坚固。 3. He makes his house, or lodge, by piling a great mass of sticks and roots in a big cone on a solid foundation at the bottom of the pond and weighting them down with mud. 它在池塘底部一个地基坚固的大锥状穴中堆积大量的树枝和草根，用泥巴压实，建造起自己的家，或者说是巢穴。 4. They were immediately admitted into the lodge. 他们立刻被让进门房。 5. You can lodge the valuables in the bank. 你可以把贵重物品存放在银行里。', '过去式: lodged 过去分词: lodged 现在分词: lodging 第三人称单数: lodges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brass', '[bræs]', 'n.黄铜(制品)；铜管（乐器）；厚脸皮 adj.黄铜的', '1. Brass is formed by the fusion of copper and zinc. 黄铜是由铜和锌熔合制成的。 2. The brass is too loud. 铜管乐器的声音太响了。 3. He walked in, bold as brass, and asked me to lend him 50! 他走进来，厚颜无耻地要我借给他50英镑！ 4. How do you have the brass to say that? 你怎么有脸那么说呢？ 5. The dwarf sat down and the elf rang the little brass bell. 侏儒坐下来，而小仙人摇了那小铜铃。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crisis', '[\'kraɪsɪs]', 'n.危机；危急关头', '1. They suffered huge losses in the financial crisis. 他们在经济危机时遭受了巨大的损失。 2. The Cabinet met to resolve the crisis. 内阁开会, 寻求解决危机的办法。 3. In this crisis, all the prejudices fell away. 值此危急时期，各种偏见均已消失。 4. She\'s always to the fore at moments of crisis. 她在危急关头总是挺身而出。', '名词复数: crises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resolve', '[rɪ\'zɑːlv]', 'vt.解决；决定；表决；分解 vi.决定；分解 n.决心；坚决', '1. Intensive efforts are being made to resolve the dispute. 现正全力以赴来解决这场纠纷。 2. He resolved that nothing should hold him back. 他下决心不让任何事情阻挡他。 3. We can resolve the problem into more elementary items. 我们能够把这个问题分解成更基本的细目。 4. He resolved on going abroad to study. 他决定到海外留学。 5. He kept his resolve to do better. 他决心干得更出色。', '形容词: resolvable 副词: resolvedly 名词: resolvability 过去式: resolved 过去分词: resolved 现在分词: resolving 第三人称单数: resolves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blouse', '[blaʊs]', 'n.女衬衫', '1. She wears a white blouse today. 今天她穿了一件白色衬衫。 2. I am interested in your silk blouse. 我对你们的丝绸女衬衫感兴趣。 3. The secretary was wearing a blue chiffon blouse. 这个秘书穿著一件蓝色的雪纺绸衬衫。', '过去式: bloused 过去分词: bloused 现在分词: blousing 第三人称单数: blouses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('learned', '[\'lɜːrnɪd]', 'adj.有学问的；博学的 动词learn的过去式和过去分词.', '1. I think he is a most learned man. 我认为他是个很有学问的人。 2. Most learned men are modest. 大部分有学问的人都很谦虚。 3. Learned men are not necessarily wise. 博学者未必都是聪明的。 4. He is a learned doctor. 他是一个医术高明的医生。', '副词: learnedly 名词: learnedness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mobile', '[\'moʊbl]', 'adj.移动的；易变的；活动的 n.<美>汽车；可动雕塑；悬挂饰物；活动物体', '1. Additionally, consumers continue to embrace mobile personal devices. 此外,消费者接受移动个人设备的热情依然不减。 2. He had a mobile, expressive, animated face. 他有一张多变的，富于表情的，生动活泼的脸。 3. He has a broken leg and isn\'t very mobile. 他的腿摔伤了,活动不便。 4. A specially equipped car makes a handicapped person more mobile. 有特殊装置的汽车使得残障者比以前更易于活动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('companion', '[kəm\'pæniən]', 'n.同伴；志趣相投的人；成对物品之一；参考书 v.陪伴', '1. He is a good companion on the journey. 他是个好旅伴。 2. He had always considered her an ideal companion for his son. 他一直以为她是他儿子的理想伴侣。 3. The dog has been her constant companion these past ten years. 过去十年来,这只狗一直与她形影不离。 4. His brother is not much of a companion for him. 他兄弟与他情趣不甚相投。 5. I worked as a companion to an old princess. 我当过一位老公爵夫人的陪伴人。', '过去式: companioned 过去分词: companioned 现在分词: companioning 第三人称单数: companions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('camel', '[\'kæml]', 'n.骆驼；浮船箱；驼色', '1. The camel is a herbivorous animal. 骆驼是一种食草动物。 2. The merchant decided to use camels to carry his goods across the desert. 商人决定用骆驼载运货物穿过沙漠。 3. The favorite, of course, is camel. 最受欢迎的自然是驼色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hungry', '[\'hʌŋɡri]', 'adj.饥饿的；渴望的', '1. The smell of bread beckoned the hungry boy. 面包香味吸引著那个饥饿的男孩。 2. A lean and hungry cat came to our door. 一只饥饿的瘦猫走到我家门口。 3. Wall Street still wants people who are hungry and pushy. 华尔街需要的是一些渴望的，积极进取的人。 4. The Friz is always hungry for adventure, and that\'s just what the class gets. 弗瑞斯老师非常喜欢外出探险，而这也正是全班同学所渴望的。', '副词: hungrily 比较级: hungrier 最高级: hungriest 名词: hungriness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cover', '[\'kʌvər]', 'n.封面；盖子；套子；表面 v.覆盖；涉及；包含；掩护；给…保险', '1. The front cover of the novel has been torn off. 这本小说的封面已被撕掉。 2. I can\'t make the cover of the tin fit on. 我无法把这罐头的盖子盖上。 3. The car should be housed with a cover for a longer time\'s parking. 长时间的存放汽车，应给汽车罩上套子。 4. Tooth-colored porcelain will cover the metal crowns. 金属表面覆盖和牙齿一样颜色地瓷。 5. Snow covered the ground. 积雪覆盖了大地。', '形容词: coverable 名词: coverer 过去式: covered 过去分词: covered 现在分词: covering 第三人称单数: covers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('horse', '[hɔːrs]', 'n.马 vt.骑马 adj.马的', '1. The horse jumped the fence. 那匹马跃过了栅栏。 2. He withdrew his horse from the race. 他让他的马退出了比赛。 3. She sat her horse well. 她善於骑马。 4. Do you like to horse with me this afternoon? 今天下午你愿意陪我去骑马吗? 5. My father bought a horse blanket. 我父亲买一条骑马用的毯子。', '过去式: horsed 过去分词: horsed 现在分词: horsing 第三人称单数: horses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('premier', '[prɪ\'mɪr]', 'n.总理；首相 adj.首位的；第一的；最初的', '1. Premier Zhou is a distinguished politician. 周总理是一位卓越的政治家。 2. The premier deals with important affairs of state. 总理处理国家重要事务。 3. The premiers of the two countries met in Geneva yesterday. 两国首相昨天在日内瓦会晤。 4. His work on the cause of the diseases is of premier importance to the whole world. 他的病理研究工作对全世界至关重要。', '名词: premiership');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('capable', '[\'keɪpəbl]', 'adj.有能力的；能干的；有...的可能性', '1. Not everyone is capable of judging art. 并不是每个人都有鉴赏艺 术的能力。 2. Only human beings are capable of speech. 只有人类才具有说话的能力。 3. Bill is rated as very capable. 大家公认比尔很能干。 4. He is a very capable administrator. 他是个十分能干的行政人员。', '副词: capably 名词: capableness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crack', '[kræk]', 'v.破裂；砸开；发出爆裂声；撞击；破解；变嘶哑；崩溃；制裁；<非正式>开玩笑 n.裂缝；裂痕；爆裂声；猛击；尝试；俏皮话 adj.训练有素的', '1. The glass will crack if you pour boiled water into it . 一倒进去滚开水，这个玻璃杯就会破裂。 2. You may crack these nuts with a hammer. 你可以用锤子把这些坚果敲开。 3. I cracked two eggs into the frying pan. 我往平底锅里打了两个鸡蛋。 4. Thunder cracked overhead. 雷在头顶上炸响了。 5. There is a crack in this window. 这扇窗户上有个裂纹。 6. She is a crack shot with a rifle. 她是步枪神枪手。', '过去式: cracked 过去分词: cracked 现在分词: cracking 第三人称单数: cracks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('emit', '[i\'mɪt]', 'vt.发出，发射；放射；吐露', '1. The cheese was emitting a strong smell. 干酪散发出强烈的气味。 2. A volcano emits smoke and ashes. 火山散发着烟和灰。 3. He was so pale that he seemed to emit a pearly glow. 他白得似乎发出像一样珍珠的微光。 4. Fireflies emit light but not heat. 萤火虫发光但不放出热。', '名词: emitter 过去式: emitted 过去分词: emitted 现在分词: emitting 第三人称单数: emits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('local', '[\'loʊkl]', 'adj.地方性的；当地的；局部的 n.当地人', '1. This is a local problem, not a nation-wide one. 这是地方性的问题，而非全国性的问题。 2. I suggest that he put an advertisement in the local paper. 我建议他在当地的报纸上登条广告。 3. He provided local delicacies for his guests\' meal. 他用当地的美味佳肴来招待客人。 4. The local war escalated into a major conflict. 局部的战争逐步升级成大规模的冲突。 5. I asked one of the locals which way to go. 我问了一位本地人，该走哪条路。', '副词: locally 名词: localness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sympathy', '[\'sɪmpəθi]', 'n.同情；同情心；同感；赞同；慰问', '1. I felt much sympathy for the blind. 我对盲人深感同情。 2. I have great sympathy for people in affliction. 我对那些受苦受难的人们充满同情。 3. The story stirred her sympathy. 这故事激起了她的同情心。 4. You shouldn\'t trade on her sympathy. 你不应该利用她的同情心。', '名词复数: sympathies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pipe', '[paɪp]', 'n.管子；烟斗；管乐器 vt.以管输送；装管道；吹奏；尖声说；(为衣服等)滚边 vi.吹奏管乐；尖叫', '1. Water is spouting out of the pipe. 水正从管子里喷出来。 2. The workers are laying pipes under the road. 工人们正在道路下面铺设管道。 3. The plumber went down to the cellar to fix the leaky pipe. 管道工到地下室去修漏水的管子。 4. He rammed the tobacco into his pipe. 他把烟丝塞进烟斗。 5. The people in the village used to pipe water . 这个村子里的人过去常以管道输送水。 6. He would pipe away on his flute all day and night. 他可以整天整夜地吹奏长笛。', '过去式: piped 过去分词: piped 现在分词: piping 第三人称单数: pipes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inn', '[ɪn]', 'n.客栈；小旅店', '1. There was an air of romance about the old inn. 这家老客栈颇有些浪漫气氛。 2. I intend to strike my staff at that small inn. 我打算在那家客栈暂住下来。 3. The traveller decided to lie at an inn that night. 旅行者决定那天晚上在一个小旅店过夜。 4. My girl friend enjoys traveling through the country hailing up at the nearest inn. 我的女朋友喜欢乡间旅行，夜宿就近的小旅店。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reap', '[riːp]', 'vt.收割；收获；获得 vi.收割', '1. The peasants are reaping a field of barley. 农民们正在收割大麦。 2. He that soweth virtue shall reap fame. 播下美德，收获名望。 3. If you plant pride, you will reap destruction. 如果你种下骄傲，你就会收获毁灭。 4. It is a season that peasants reap the corn from what they planted in spring. 农民们春季播种玉米，现在是他们收获的季节。 5. They that sow in tears shall reap in joy. 流泪撒种的必欢呼收割。', '过去式: reaped 过去分词: reaped 现在分词: reaping 第三人称单数: reaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('read', '[riːd]', 'v.识字；阅读；朗读；理解；读到；猜测；读唇语；写着；读起来（给人以某种印象）；显示；看读数；听到；将...改为；攻读；（计算机）读盘 n.阅读；好读物 adj.博学的；熟知的', '1. Only a few of the children there can read. 那里只有几个小孩识字。 2. Read the text slowly and deliberately. 缓慢,有意的读全文。 3. Every man is a volume if you know how to read him. 每一个人都是一卷书,只要你懂得如何阅读它。 4. Please read aloud so that I can hear you. 请大声朗读，好让我能听到。 5. I was having a quiet read when the phone rang. 我在静静地看书，忽然电话铃响了。 6. He is very widely read in law. 他在法律方面知识渊博。', '过去式: read 过去分词: read 现在分词: reading 第三人称单数: reads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('embark', '[ɪm\'bɑːrk]', 'v.乘船；装载；着手；从事', '1. We embarked for Calais at midday. 我们中午乘船去加来。 2. Passengers with cars must embark first. 带汽车的乘客必须先上船。 3. The cargo ship will embark the unloaded freight from the draft trucks. 货船将会装载载重卡车卸下的货物。 4. The ship embarked passengers and food at a Spanish port. 这艘船在西班牙的一个港口装载了乘客和食品。', '名词: embarkation 过去式: embarked 过去分词: embarked 现在分词: embarking 第三人称单数: embarks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('architecture', '[\'ɑːrkɪtektʃər]', 'n.建筑学；结构；一座建筑物；总称建筑物；建筑风格；【计算机】计算机构造，架构，体系结构，结构格式', '1. He obtained a diploma in architecture. 他获得了建筑学的学位证书。 2. The architecture of this house is very substantial. 这座房子的结构很牢固。 3. The new house he bought was colonial architecture. 他新买的房子是美国初期的建筑。 4. The Forbidden City is one of the world\'s greatest works of architecture. 紫禁城是世界上最伟大的建筑之一。', '形容词: architectural 副词: architecturally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exciting', '[ɪk\'saɪtɪŋ]', 'adj.令人兴奋的；使人激动的', '1. I like the exciting rhythm of African drum music. 我喜欢非洲鼓乐的令人兴奋的节奏。 2. So exciting was the game that I forgot all about the coming finals. 比赛是如此令人兴奋，以致我把即将来临的期末考忘得一乾二净。 3. That was the most exciting film of the year. 那是一年中最令人兴奋的一部影片。 4. This is a very exciting book. 这是一本非常扣人心弦的书。', '副词: excitingly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('no', '[noʊ]', 'adv.不 adj.没有；不是；禁止 n.否定的回答；投反对票者', '1. The sick man is no better. 那病人一点也没有好转。 2. You are very selfish sometimes.---No,I\'m not. 你有时很自私的。--不,我不自私。 3. He has no money. 他没有钱。 4. There is no water on the moon. 月球上一点水也没有。 5. It\'s time for us to say \"No\" to America. 是我们对美国说不的时候了。', '名词复数: noes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('respective', '[rɪ\'spektɪv]', 'adj.分别的；各自的', '1. He drove them both to their respective homes. 他驾车把他们分别送到家里。 2. The three men were given work according to their respective abilities. 这三个人根据各自的能力被分配了工作。 3. Product name is trademark or registered trademark of their respective owner. 产品名称为它们各自所有者的商标或注册商标。', '名词: respectiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('month', '[mʌnθ]', 'n.月，月份', '1. He shut himself away for a month to catch up on his academic work. 他与世隔绝一个月，力图把功课赶上去。 2. He\'s asking 80 a month rent for that flat. 那套房间月租他要80英镑。 3. July is the hottest month in a year in my hometown. 在我的家乡，七月是一年里最热的一月。 4. His baby is six months old. 他的孩子有六个月大了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yes', '[jes]', 'adv.是；是的 n.是（表示肯定） v.对…说是', '1. Yes, monsieur. 是，先生。 2. Yes, you\'re quite right. 是的，你很对。 3. Yes, I don\'t see why not. 是的，我看不出有什么不好。 4. Yes, it\'s still in my mind. 是的，这事仍在我的记忆里。 5. Answer yes or no. 回答是或者不是。 6. The boy kept yessing when his father was talking with him. 那个男孩在他爸爸对他说话时连声说是。', '名词复数: yeses 过去式: yessed 过去分词: yessed 现在分词: yessing 第三人称单数: yeses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('civil', '[\'sɪvl]', 'adj.公民的；文明的；国内的；民用的；民事的；【建】土木的', '1. The law shall strictly protect civil rights. 法律应严格保护公民的权利。 2. The presence of the army should act as a check on civil unrest. 军队的存在应能制止民间的动乱。 3. The boy was so cold and even didn\'t return a civil greeting. 那个男孩是那么的冷淡,他甚至都没有回敬一个礼貌的问候。 4. The America Civil War broke out during the presidency of Lincoln. 在林肯就职其间,美国爆发了内战。', '副词: civilly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extend', '[ɪk\'stend]', 'v.延伸；延长；伸展；扩展；提供；使竭尽全力', '1. Our playing fields extend as far as those trees. 我们的操场延伸到那些树前。 2. Theoretically, a line can extend into infinity. 从理论上来说直线可以无限地延伸。 3. How to extend a visa if it expires? 签证到期后怎样延长签证? 4. Dry-cleaning can extend the life of your clothing. 干洗可以延长衣服的使用寿命。', '形容词: extendable 名词: extendibility 过去式: extended 过去分词: extended 现在分词: extending 第三人称单数: extends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tug', '[tʌɡ]', 'n.用力拉；拖船 v.用力拉', '1. Tom felt a tug at his sleeve. 汤姆觉得有人拉了拉他的衣袖。 2. Tom gave his sister\'s hair a hard tug. 汤姆使劲地扯了一下他姐姐的头发。 3. We had a great tug to persuade him. 我们费了很大的精力去劝服他。 4. The tug will lead the liner into the harbor. 拖船将把那艘客轮引入港口。 5. She tried to tug my hand away. 她试图把我的手拉开。', '名词: tugger 过去式: tugged 过去分词: tugged 现在分词: tugging 第三人称单数: tugs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wander', '[\'wɑːndər]', 'vi.漫步；蜿蜒；迷路；闲逛；徘徊 vt.漫步于 n.漫游；徘徊；闲逛', '1. He likes to wander over the countryside. 他喜欢在乡间漫步。 2. The river wanders through some beautiful country. 这条河蜿蜒曲折地流经一些风景秀丽的乡村。 3. I like to wander in the park after dinner. 我喜欢晚饭后在公园里闲逛。 4. The boy was wandering around. 男孩在那周围徘徊。 5. The travelers are wandering the forests and fields. 旅行者漫步穿过森林与田野。 6. She went for a little wander round the park. 她到公园去遛达遛达。', '副词: wanderingly 名词: wanderer 过去式: wandered 过去分词: wandered 现在分词: wandering 第三人称单数: wanders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ego', '[\'iːɡoʊ]', 'n.自我；自负；自尊心', '1. We can\'t transcend the limitations of the ego. 我们无法超越自我的局限性。 2. Mind consists of three parts: id, ego and superego. 人的思想意识由三部分构成:以德,自我和超我。 3. He has the biggest ego of anyone I\'ve ever met. 他是我所见的最自负的人。 4. His ego was tickled by the implicit flattery of the journalist\'s attention. 那个记者的蓄意奉承使他的自负得到了满足。', '名词复数: egos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('economy', '[ɪ\'kɑːnəmi]', 'n.经济；节约 adj.经济的；廉价的', '1. The state of the economy is very worrying. 目前的经济状况令人十分担忧。 2. The determinate factor of our economy is to control inflation. 我们经济的决定性因素是控制通货膨胀。 3. The last five years have seen a consistent improvement in the country\'s economy. 在最近的五年里，这个国家的经济状况一直在好转。 4. She preached economy as the best means of solving the crisis. 她大力鼓吹节约是解决危机的关键。 5. An economy class air ticket is fit for ordinary workers, because it costs much less. 经济舱机票对一般工作人员比较合适,因为它的价格要便宜得多。', '名词复数: economies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fantastic', '[fæn\'tæstɪk]', 'adj.极好的；巨大的；奇异的；难以置信的；幻想的', '1. We watched a fantastic play yesterday evening. 昨天晚上我们看了一场非常精彩的演出。 2. I have a fantastic amount of work to do. 我有大量的工作要做。 3. My daughter likes to describe her fantastic dreams to me. 我女儿喜欢给我讲她那些奇怪的梦。 4. It is so fantastic that a child of 5 can speak so good English. 真难以置信,一个五岁的孩子英语竟然说得这么好。', '副词: fantastically 异体字: fantastical 名词: fantasticality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('summary', '[\'sʌməri]', 'n.摘要；总结 adj.简略的；概要的；即决的', '1. Please write me a summary of this report. 请替我写一份这份报告的摘要。 2. Your summary will need fleshing out before you present it. 你的总结需要增加一些具体材料再交出。 3. I went through by a summary method. 我成功运用了一个简易的方法。 4. He gave a summary report of the day\'s events. 他对一天的事件作了简要的报告。', '副词: summarily 名词: summariness 名词复数: summaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('supply', '[sə\'plaɪ]', 'n.供应；补给；贮备 vt.供应；提供；补充', '1. They wrote off for a fresh supply of penicillin. 他们发信要求再供应一批青霉素。 2. Our wood supply proved insufficient. 我们的木材供应证明是不够的。 3. A tight blockade cut Napoleon\'s supply lines. 严密的封锁切断了拿破仑的补给线。 4. Cannon cannot be towed by supply trucks. 火炮不能被补给车牵引。 5. They wrote off for a fresh supply of penicillin. 他们发信要求再供应一批青霉素。', '名词: supplier 名词复数: supplies 过去式: supplied 过去分词: supplied 现在分词: supplying 第三人称单数: supplies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diameter', '[daɪ\'æmɪtər]', 'n.直径', '1. The diameter of the tree-trunk is about 2 meters. 这树干的直径大约是2米。 2. We must gauge the diameter of wire first. 我们必须先测量电线的直径。 3. The axis of a circle is its diameter. 圆的轴线是其直径。', '形容词: diametral');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('palace', '[\'pæləs]', 'n.宫殿；豪华住宅；王室；大的公共建筑(如旅馆、影院等)', '1. There are many flocks of tourists in the palace. 宫殿里有好几群游客。 2. Have you been to the Imperial Palace? 你去过故宫吗？ 3. The carriage passed through the palace gate. 马车进入了宫殿的大门。 4. Compared to ours their house is a palace. 他们的房子和我们的相比简直太豪华了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('majesty', '[\'mædʒəsti]', 'n.最高权威；威严；庄严 Majesty: 陛下.', '1. Policemen and judges uphold the majesty of the law. 警察和法官维护法律的权威。 2. Even in great adversity, he kept his majesty. 既使身处绝境，他仍保持自己的威严。 3. The king had unspeakable majesty. 国王有无法形容的威严。 4. The majesty of the occasion thrilled us all. 那庄严的场面使我们每个人都激动不已。 5. I\'m not a very good rider, Your Majesty. 我可不是个好骑手，陛下。', '名词复数: majesties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('navy', '[\'neɪvi]', 'n.海军；船队；海军蓝', '1. He is a gunner of the British navy. 他是英国海军的一名炮手。 2. Beiyang Navy is the earliest naval force of China. 北洋水师是中国最早的海军部队。 3. The army, navy and airforce are all controlled by the Ministry of Defense. 陆海空军皆由国防部控制。 4. What I have said about the army also applies, mutatis mutandis, to the navy. 我谈到的陆军方面,如作适当变动,也适用于海军。', '名词复数: navies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sausage', '[\'sɔːsɪdʒ]', 'n.香肠；腊肠', '1. She loves sausage and mash. 她喜欢香肠和土豆泥。 2. Many people don\'t like blood sausage. 很多人不喜欢黑香肠。 3. The sausage began to spit in the pan. 锅里香肠开始滋滋作响。 4. I\'ll take a pound of that sausage. 我买一磅那种腊肠。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spaceship', '[\'speɪsʃɪp]', 'n.宇宙飞船', '1. The computer decelerated the spaceship. 计算机使宇宙飞船减速。 2. Spaceship make it possible to travel to the moon. 宇宙飞船使去月球旅行成为可能。', '异体字: spaceship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('precaution', '[prɪ\'kɔːʃn]', 'n.预防；预防措施', '1. You should take an umbrella just as a precaution. 你该带把伞，有备无患。 2. I took the precaution of locking everything in the safe. 我把一切东西都锁在保险箱里以防万一。 3. The report is scathing about the lack of safety precaution. 该报道对缺乏安全预防措施一事严加指责。 4. All this wake the local government to the need for safety precaution. 所有这些使当地政府认识到必须采取安全预防措施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trip', '[trɪp]', 'n.旅行；摔倒；差错；轻快的步伐 vt.使跌倒；使失败；使犯错；起锚；竖帆 vi.绊倒；旅行；轻快地走；失误；结巴', '1. They planned to make a wedding trip to Paris. 他们计划到巴黎旅行度蜜月。 2. He who carries three baskets must put one on his head, which is apt to tumble and trip him up. 有三只篮子的人就得把一只篮子顶在头上，这样很容易摔倒。 3. He tried to trip me up. 他想把我绊倒。 4. He tripped on a tree root. 他被一株树根绊倒了。', '过去式: tripped 过去分词: tripped 现在分词: tripping 第三人称单数: trips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('metric', '[\'metrɪk]', 'adj.公制的；米制的；十进制的 n.标准；度量', '1. Britain changed to a metric system of currency in 1970. 1970年,英国已改用公制货币。 2. Most countries adopt metric system. 大多数国家采用米制。 3. Government departments use metric units exclusively. 政府部门现已全面采用十进制单位。 4. Extensibility is a difficult metric to gauge. 可扩展性是一个比较难衡量的标准。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('troublesome', '[\'trʌblsəm]', 'adj.令人烦恼的；讨厌的；困难的；棘手的', '1. You must learn to rid yourself of such troublesome thoughts. 你必须学会使自己摆脱如此令人烦恼的想法。 2. She has left, for instance, some troublesome bits of scaffolding, like the vermiform appendix, behind. 比如，它遗留下了令人烦恼的残留物，如隐藏的阑尾。 3. This species is a troublesome weed. 本种是一根令人讨厌的杂草。 4. He hoped in this way to get rid of the troublesome prisoner. 他指望这样除掉这个讨厌的囚犯。', '副词: troublesomely 名词: troublesomeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gossip', '[\'ɡɑːsɪp]', 'n.流言蜚语；爱说长道短的人；闲话 vi.散播(流言蜚语)', '1. There has been much gossip in political circles. 政界里有许多流言蜚语。 2. I loathe people who spread malicious gossip. 我讨厌那些散布充满恶意的流言蜚语的人。 3. He\'s a terrible gossip. 他专爱说人闲话。 4. I have no time to engage in gossip. 我无暇闲聊。 5. She loves to gossip to her neighbors. 她喜欢议论邻居们的是非长短。', '形容词: gossipy 名词: gossiper 过去式: gossiped 过去分词: gossiped 现在分词: gossiping 第三人称单数: gossips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('astonish', '[ə\'stɑːnɪʃ]', 'vt.使惊讶；使吃惊', '1. I was astonished at the news of his escape. 听到他逃之夭夭的消息，我感到惊讶。 2. She astonished me with her beautiful handwriting. 她以其秀丽的书法而使我惊异。 3. A matter of repeated occurrence like this will not astonish people. 重复出现的事物不会使人吃惊。', '副词: astonishingly 过去式: astonished 过去分词: astonished 现在分词: astonishing 第三人称单数: astonishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ideal', '[aɪ\'diːəl]', 'adj.理想的；完美的；空想的；观念的 n.理想；典范；目标', '1. It is an ideal day for a picnic. 这是一个出外野餐的理想日子。 2. He is looking for a wife but he hasn\'t found his ideal mate. 他正在寻找未来的妻子，但还没有找到理想人选。 3. The facilities were not ideal but we managed as best we could. 设备不理想，但我们已经尽了最大的努力。 4. It\'s my ideal of what a family home should be. 这是我心目中完美的家庭住宅。 5. She \'s looking for a job, but hasn\'t found her ideal yet. 她在找工作,但是还没有找到理想的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pact', '[pækt]', 'n.契约；协定；条约', '1. It was a pact made in fun long ago. 这是很久以前在开玩笑时定下的契约。 2. Tell Me Why You and I must make a pact. 你和我必须订立契约。 3. They made a pact not to tell anyone. 他们有协定，不告诉任何人。 4. They ratify the pact because they think it will bring peace. 他们批准了这项协定，因为他们认为它将能带来和平。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bride', '[braɪd]', 'n.新娘', '1. The bride wore a beautiful white dress. 新娘穿了一身美丽的白色礼服。 2. We must drink to the health of the bride. 我们要为新娘的健康干杯。 3. The bride brought many dowries to her husband. 新娘带着很多嫁妆给她丈夫。 4. The bride was given away by her father. 由父亲把新娘交与新郎。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('index', '[\'ɪndeks]', 'n.指数；索引；(刻度盘上的)指针 v.指出；编索引', '1. Do you know the price index in the city? 你知道这个城市的物价指数吗？ 2. The index is arranged in alphabetical order. 这索引是按字母顺序排列的。 3. The handler for this event receives the column index and row index of the mouse pointer position. 此事件的处理程序接收鼠标指针所在位置的列索引和行索引。 4. The pointer from an index row in a nonclustered index to a data row is called a row locator. 从非聚集索引中的索引行指向数据行的指针称为行定位器。 5. Wrinkles index advancing age. 皱纹显示出年岁在增加。', '名词: indexer 名词复数: indexes 过去式: indexed 过去分词: indexed 现在分词: indexing 第三人称单数: indexes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acrobat', '[\'ækrəbæt]', 'n.杂技演员；见风使舵的人', '1. The acrobat\'s feat took the audience\'s breath away. 杂技演员的惊险动作使观众为之咋舌。', '形容词: acrobatic 副词: acrobatically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('session', '[\'seʃn]', 'n.会议；会期；开庭期；学期；一段时间', '1. If the negotiations between the rich northerly nations and poor southerly nations make headway, it is intended that a ministerial session in December should be arranged. 要是北方富国和南方穷国之间的谈判获得进展的话,就打算在十二月份安排召开部长级的会议。 2. Several bills were enacted at the end of this session of Parliament. 这届国会结束时，好几个议案制定成为法律。 3. Is Parliament in session during the summer? 议会在夏季是开会期吗? 4. Be seated! This court is now in session. 请坐下！本庭现在开庭。', '形容词: sessional 副词: sessionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('orbit', '[\'ɔːrbɪt]', 'n.势力范围；眼眶；轨迹 vt.绕轨道而行；进入轨道 vi.盘旋', '1. Hou Kou district fell into Japanese orbit before the outbreak of the second sino-Japan war. 虹口区在抗日战争爆发前就已落入日本人手中。 2. In the right orbit, an external ethmoidectomy was done, while in the left, a transnasal endoscopic approach was used to remove the inferomedial wall. 两边皆以外侧眼眶切开术行外侧眼窝减压术合并内侧及部分眼窝底减压术。 3. Conclusions For patients undergoing enophthalmos caused by a crepitant frature in orbit, it is the best way to perform an operation as early as possible. 结论对于眼眶爆裂性骨折引起的眼球内陷可考虑早期手术，其效果优于晚期手术者。 4. The spacecraft is in orbit around the moon. 该航天器在绕月球轨道运行。 5. The space shuttle will orbit a weather satellite. 太空梭将把一个气象卫星送入运行轨道。 6. Make one more orbit to the left again. 左转弯再盘旋一圈。', '过去式: orbited 过去分词: orbited 现在分词: orbiting 第三人称单数: orbits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('system', '[\'sɪstəm]', 'n.系统；体系；身体；制度', '1. The drainage system has been aged. 排水系统已经老化了。 2. The magazine is produced using a desktop publishing system. 这本杂志用一个桌面的出版系统做出来的。 3. They are introducing a very sophisticated system for delivering information. 他们正在介绍一个非常复杂的传递信息的体系。 4. Excessive drinking does harm to the system. 过度饮酒对身体有害。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interpret', '[ɪn\'tɜːrprɪt]', 'v.口译；解释；翻译；诠释', '1. To interpret at the UN is a difficult task. 在联合国做口译是件难 度很大的差事. 2. We need somebody to interpret from Russian into English. 我们需要一个把俄语口译为英语的人。 3. She interpret his silence as arrogance. 她把他的沉默解释为傲慢。 4. The guide interpreted the woman\'s remarks for us. 向导把那个女人的话翻译给我们听。', '形容词: interpretable 名词: interpretability 过去式: interpreted 过去分词: interpreted 现在分词: interpreting 第三人称单数: interprets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('say', '[seɪ]', 'v.说；讲；比如说；表明 n.发言权；意见', '1. He said hello to me with a smile. 他面带微笑地和我打了个招呼。 2. She said that she liked singing. 她说她喜欢唱歌。 3. He will of course say yes to my proposal. 他一定会同意我的建议的。 4. Be quiet, I\'ve something to say to you. 安静, 我有话要对你们讲。 5. We are considering giving them greater say in such matters. 我们正考虑在这样的事情上给他们更多的发言权。', '名词: sayer 过去式: said 过去分词: said 现在分词: saying 第三人称单数: says');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crystal', '[\'krɪstl]', 'n.水晶；结晶体；表蒙子 adj.透明的；晶体的', '1. I lost my crystal necklace at the party. 我在晚会上丢失了水晶项链。 2. This set of crystal wine cups is very expensive. 这套水晶玻璃酒杯非常昂贵。 3. This kind of crystal takes the shape of an irregular rhombus. 这种结晶体呈不规则菱形。 4. Can you fit me up with a new watch crystal? 你能给装一块新的表蒙玻璃吗? 5. The bird flew into the crystal clear window. 这只小鸟撞上了完全透明的窗户。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('here', '[hɪr]', 'adv.这里；这时；在这点上 n.这里 int.嘿；喂（用于引起注意）', '1. It is neither hot nor cold in winter here. 这里冬天既不热也不冷。 2. He has lived here for the last few years. 过去的几年他一直住在这里。 3. Here he stopped reading and looked up. 这时他停止看书,抬头看了看。 4. The bell here rang for the third time. 这时,铃声第三次响起来了。 5. From here on the story gets more interesting. 故事从这往后更加有趣。 6. Here, catch hold of this parcel. 嘿，接住这个包。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ten', '[ten]', 'num.十', '1. He has been an exile for ten years. 他已经流亡十年。 2. The dictator met his doom after ten years of rule. 独裁者统治了十年终於完蛋了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('minimize', '[\'mɪnɪmaɪz]', 'v.将 ... 减到最少；贬低', '1. Governments consider it prudent to minimize the risk. 各国政府均认为把这种危害降低到最小程度的做法是明智的。 2. The polar explorers took every precaution to minimize the dangers of their trip. 极地探险者十分小心谨慎，以便使旅途的危险性减少到最小。 3. A sound approach to the problem is to minimize the number of parts. 正确解决这一问题的方法是把零件的数目减至最少。 4. He minimized the value of her contribution to his research so that he got all the praise. 他极力贬低她在那项研究中的贡献，从而独获全部奖励。', '名词: minimization 过去式: minimized 过去分词: minimized 现在分词: minimizing 第三人称单数: minimizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recovery', '[rɪ\'kʌvəri]', 'n.恢复；痊愈；复原；重获', '1. We are surprised by the rapidity of her recovery. 她恢复得那么快，我们都有些惊讶。 2. He is well on his way to recovery. 他正在顺利恢复。 3. A lot has been done in the recovery of national economy in the past few years. 在过去的几年中我们为了国民经济的恢复做了大量的工作。 4. The doctors held out no hope of recovery. 医生们对痊愈不抱希望。', '名词复数: recoveries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('socialism', '[\'soʊʃəlɪzəm]', 'n.社会主义', '1. From then on we proceeded to build socialism. 从那时起,我们开始建设社会主义。 2. Who is the founder of the scientific socialism? 谁是科学社会主义的奠基人？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('why', '[waɪ]', 'adv.为什么 conj.... 的理由；为什么 int.咳；哎呀 n.理由；谜', '1. The reasons why he did it are obscure. 他做那事的理由还不清楚。 2. That is why I am not in favour of the plan. 那是我不赞成这个计划的理由。 3. He expounded the reasons why he did it. 他阐述了他做这件事的理由。 4. She knows why the metal is the good conductor. 她知道金属为什么是好的导体。 5. Why, it\'s nearly nine o\'clock. 啊, 快要九点了。 6. I cannot explain why. 我说不出理由。', '名词复数: whys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('follow', '[\'fɑːloʊ]', 'v.跟随；追赶；紧接着；注意；遵循；沿着；明白', '1. The little boy followed his father out. 小男孩跟随他父亲出去了。 2. They blew up the bridge so that the enemy couldn\'t follow them. 他们炸毁了桥梁,使敌人无法追赶他们。 3. If you ignore your diet, trouble will follow. 如果你忽视自己的饮食，必然会遇到麻烦 4. He followed every word of the trial. 他注意听着裁判的每句话。', '过去式: followed 过去分词: followed 现在分词: following 第三人称单数: follows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('immerse', '[ɪ\'mɜːrs]', 'vt.浸；陷入', '1. I immerse my clothes in the water. 我把衣服浸在水里。 2. Please immerse the plant in water for a few minutes. 把那棵植物在水里浸泡几分钟。 3. He immersed himself totally in his work. 他埋头于工作。 4. I immerse myself into reciting English vocabulary. 我专心于背英语词汇。', '过去式: immersed 过去分词: immersed 现在分词: immersing 第三人称单数: immerses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enhance', '[ɪn\'hæns]', 'vt.提高；增加；加强', '1. He made many efforts to enhance his reputation. 他做了许多努力来提高他的声誉。 2. Martial education is an important means to exercise volition and enhance national defense notion. 提出军事教育是锻炼意志,提高国防观念的重要手段。 3. This year, we will review the functions and other aspects of District Councils and enhance our support for them. 今年将展开对区议会功能等方面的检讨,增加对区议会的支持。 4. The programme aims to enhance the employment of young people with disabilities or early signs of mental illness. 计划的目的,是加强残疾或出现精神病早期徵状的青少年的就业能力。', '形容词: enhancive 名词: enhancement 过去式: enhanced 过去分词: enhanced 现在分词: enhancing 第三人称单数: enhances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pharmacy', '[\'fɑːrməsi]', 'n.药房；药剂学', '1. Please go to emergency pharmacy for your medicines. 请到急诊药房取药。 2. He is a shop assistant at a Chinese pharmacy. 他是中药房的售货员。 3. He just was engaged in the pharmacy 16 years old. 他十六岁就从事药学。 4. Clinical pharmacy is a new specialty in China. 临床药学在我国是个新兴的专业。', '名词复数: pharmacies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('waste', '[weɪst]', 'n.废物；浪费；荒地 v.浪费；滥用；消耗 adj.荒芜的；无用的；浪费的', '1. The city waste is disposed of in the sea. 城市垃圾倒在海里处理掉。 2. The safe disposal of nuclear waste is a major problem. 安全处置核废料是个大问题。 3. It\'s only a waste of time to speak to her. 和她说话纯粹是浪费时间。 4. The routine work is a waste of her talents. 做这样千篇一律的工作,是浪费了她的才能。 5. All his efforts were wasted. 他的所有努力都白费了。 6. They are turning waste land into paddy fields. 他们正在使荒地变为稻田。', '过去式: wasted 过去分词: wasted 现在分词: wasting 第三人称单数: wastes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('please', '[pliːz]', 'adv.请（=plz） v.使高兴；使满意；愿意；取悦', '1. Please come with me. 请跟我来。 2. Please call if you require assistance. 如果需要帮忙，请打电话。 3. Please fill in the arrival card. 请填写这张入境卡。 4. It is better to please a fool than to anger him. 惹得傻瓜发火，不如使他快乐。', '名词: pleaser 过去式: pleased 过去分词: pleased 现在分词: pleasing 第三人称单数: pleases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('captive', '[\'kæptɪv]', 'n.俘虏；迷恋者 adj.被俘的；被迷住的', '1. The captive was whooped and jeered. 俘虏被叱责讥笑。 2. We were held captive for three months. 我们当了三个月俘虏。 3. If a hero is of any importance, Homer also mentions the captive girl with whom he shares his tent and his bed. 荷马的史诗每提到一个重要的英雄，都要讲到同他共享帐篷和枕席的被俘的姑娘。 4. With full knowledge that the experiments were conducted on captive humans, the U.S. recruited the doctors to work for them. 在充分了解到在被俘的人身上进行的实验，美国招募了这批医生为他们工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cliff', '[klɪf]', 'n.悬崖；峭壁', '1. The sea had undermined the cliff. 海水侵蚀了悬崖的基部。 2. He couldn\'t find a hold on the cliff. 他在悬崖上找不到一个可以站住脚的地方。 3. The narrow path zigzags up the cliff. 这条狭窄的小径曲曲折折地向峭壁伸延。 4. They slowly clawed their way up the cliff. 他们缓慢地爬上峭壁。', '形容词: cliffy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('master', '[\'mæstər]', 'n.主人；硕士；专家 vt.控制；精通 adj.主要的；主人的；精通的', '1. The dog remained faithful to his master. 这条狗始终忠于它的主人。 2. I can be a master of myself in learning. 我可以做自我学习上的主人。 3. He is a Master of Science. 他是理科硕士。 4. No man is born a master of art. 没有人生来就是艺术大师。 5. She learned to master her anger. 她学会了控制自己不发火。 6. There is always a master for each of these services and there may be one or more replicas. 对于这些服务的每一种总是有一个主要的而且可能有一件以上的复制品。', '名词: masterdom 过去式: mastered 过去分词: mastered 现在分词: mastering 第三人称单数: masters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flood', '[flʌd]', 'v.淹没；充满 n.洪水', '1. The cellar floods whenever it rains heavily. 一下大雨地窖里就灌满了水。 2. The river had burst its banks and flooded the valley. 河水冲破堤岸,淹没了山谷。 3. The office was flooded with complaints. 办事处收到如洪水般涌至的投诉信件。 4. Japanese cars have flooded the American market. 日本汽车已充斥美国市场。 5. Her child was washed away in the flood. 她的孩子让洪水给冲走了。', '过去式: flooded 过去分词: flooded 现在分词: flooding 第三人称单数: floods');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outbreak', '[\'aʊtbreɪk]', 'n.爆发；暴动', '1. There has been an outbreak of typhoid. 那儿正爆发伤寒。 2. The research project fetched up because of the outbreak of the war. 由于战争爆发，这个研究计划搁浅了。 3. The hospital wards were fumigated after the outbreak of typhus. 发现斑疹伤寒以后，医院的病房进行了烟熏消毒。 4. The outbreak of riot caused many people to die. 暴乱的发生使很多人丧生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('main', '[meɪn]', 'adj.主要的；最重要的 n.干线；总管道；[pl](水、煤、电)供应系统；<古>大海', '1. The teacher asked me to note down the main points of the speech. 老师要求我把演说的要点记下来。 2. The speech was most disappointing,it skirted round all the main questions. 这篇演讲非常令人失望,它回避了所有主要的问题。 3. By defeating their main competitor this firm has cornered the wheat market. 这家公司击败了主要的竞争对手而垄断了整个小麦市场。 4. The main road was flooded so we had to go round by narrow country lanes. 公路干线遭水淹没，我们只得择乡间小径绕行。 5. The main of their investments was lost in the war. 他们的大部分投资在战争中损失了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('decisive', '[dɪ\'saɪsɪv]', 'adj.决定性的；果断的', '1. The enemy was defeated in a decisive battle. 敌人在一场决定性的战斗中被击败。 2. His opinion is decisive on the question. 他对这个问题的意见是决定性的。 3. She handles affairs in a decisive manner. 她办事果断。 4. A decisive person is needed to decide this matter. 需要一个果断的人来决定这件事。', '副词: decisively 名词: decisiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('addition', '[ə\'dɪʃn]', 'n.增加；加法；附加物', '1. In addition to a diet, she pursues various exercises on TV. 节食以外她还随电视做体操。 2. In addition to an album, I gave him a pen and a pencil. 除了一本照相簿外，我还给了他一支钢笔和一支铅笔。 3. They eat a great deal of fruit in addition. 他们还吃大量的水果。 4. Addition and division are forms of computation. 加法和除法都是计算方法。', '形容词: additional 副词: additionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('advice', '[əd\'vaɪs]', 'n.劝告；忠告；建议', '1. Tell me the reason (why) he refused to listen to my advice. 告诉我为何他拒绝听从我的劝告。 2. He disregarded his doctor\'s advice. 他无视医生的劝告。 3. I set a high value on his advice. 我认为他的忠告很有价值。 4. I asked the teacher for her advice. 我征求这位老师的意见。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cheer', '[tʃɪr]', 'n.欢呼；激励；愉快 vt.鼓舞；加油；快活起来 vi.欢呼；使振奋', '1. The audience greet his speech with loud cheer. 听众对他的演讲报以高声欢呼。 2. The audience gave a great cheer when he scored. 当他得分的时候，观众们爆发出热烈的欢呼。 3. The doctor spoke words of cheer to the sick child. 医生向病童说了一些鼓励的话。 4. Your words of cheer disposed me for the task. 你的一番鼓励的话使我乐意接受这项任务了。 5. The crowd cheered the runners on as they started the last lap. 赛跑进入最後一圈时，观众为运动员加油鼓劲。 6. The crowd cheered loudly as the Queen appeared. 女王出现时群众高声欢呼。', '副词: cheeringly 名词: cheerer 过去式: cheered 过去分词: cheered 现在分词: cheering 第三人称单数: cheers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('testimony', '[\'testɪmoʊni]', 'n.证明；证据', '1. His hearty laughter is testimony of his happiness. 他尽情的欢笑可以证明他很幸福。 2. Nothing could refute her testimony that the driver was drunk. 她关于那个司机已经喝醉的证词无可辩驳。 3. The witness is giving false testimony. 那个证人在作伪证。 4. The statement is confirmed by testimony. 这个说法由证据所证实了。', '名词复数: testimonies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trace', '[treɪs]', 'n.痕迹；微量；踪迹 v.追踪；描绘；找出根源', '1. When the police exhume the corpse they discover trace of poison in it 警方掘出尸体, 发现有中毒的痕迹 2. Traces of blood were found in the bathroom. 在浴室里发现一点血。 3. The police have detected the trace of the murderer after several days of investigation. 警察经过几天的调查,发现了凶手的踪迹。 4. He traces his descent back to an old norman family. 他追踪自己的世系上溯至一个古老的诺曼家族。', '形容词: traceable 副词: traceably 名词: traceability 过去式: traced 过去分词: traced 现在分词: tracing 第三人称单数: traces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pursue', '[pər\'suː]', 'v.追求；追捕；继续执行；从事', '1. Everyone has the freedom to pursue their dreams. 每个人都有追求各自梦想的自由。 2. The police are pursuing an escaped prisoner. 警方正在追捕一名越狱的逃犯。 3. Let\'s not pursue this argument. 让我们别再继续这个争论了。 4. She wishes to pursue a medical career. 她希望从事医学工作。', '形容词: pursuable 名词: pursuer 过去式: pursued 过去分词: pursued 现在分词: pursuing 第三人称单数: pursues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('publicity', '[pʌb\'lɪsəti]', 'n.公众的注意；宣传；宣扬；宣传品；广告', '1. All the publicity nearly sent him crazy. 成天生活在公众的注意之下让他差一点发疯了。 2. The film star\'s marriage got a lot of publicity. 那位影星的婚礼引起了公众的广泛注意。 3. His zeal was damped by the apathy of the public . 公众的冷漠使他灰心丧气。 4. Voters have been distanced from the party by adverse publicity. 选民受到反面宣传的影响，对这个政党冷淡了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hide', '[haɪd]', 'v.藏；隐瞒；遮避 vt.鞭打 n.兽皮', '1. I hid the broken plate behind the table. 我把打碎的盘子藏在餐桌后面了。 2. I hide the message in a cleave in the rock. 我把情报藏在石块的裂缝里。 3. She tried to hide her feelings. 她设法不表露自己的感情。 4. The future is hidden from us. 未来是我们难以预卜的。 5. The boots are made of buffalo hide. 这双靴子是由水牛皮制成的。', '过去式: hid 过去分词: hidden/hid 现在分词: hiding 第三人称单数: hides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('multiple', '[\'mʌltɪpl]', 'adj.多种多样的；许多的 n.倍数；并联', '1. He is the person with multiple injuries. 他就是那个多处受伤的人。 2. A multiple crash can often be seen on that motorway. 那条公路上的联环撞车事故很多。 3. Words can have multiple meanings. 词汇可以有许多释义。 4. 10 is a multiple of 5. 10是5的倍数。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bridge', '[brɪdʒ]', 'n.桥梁；纽带；桥牌；鼻梁；（音乐）琴马；齿桥 vt.架桥；渡过；缩短...差距', '1. The bridge is not strong enough to allow the passage of vehicles. 这座桥不够牢固，车辆不能通行。 2. I think I\'m lost; I can\'t find the bridge. 我想我是迷路了，我找不到那座桥了。 3. They are a link to the past and a bridge to the future. 它们是联系过去的纽带，又是通向未来的桥梁。 4. The new bridge will link the Olympic Village with the rest of the Olympic Park. 这座新桥将会成为连接奥运村和余下奥林匹克公园的纽带。 5. They will bridge it over with planks. 他们将用木板在其上方架桥。', '形容词: bridgeable 过去式: bridged 过去分词: bridged 现在分词: bridging 第三人称单数: bridges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('neighborhood', '[\'neɪbəˌhʊd]', 'n.邻近；邻居；附近', '1. There is no such man in our neighborhood. 在我们的邻近没有这样的人。 2. This neighborhood is quiet peaceful! 这邻近一带很安静平和。 3. The whole neighborhood praises him. 四周邻居都称赞他。 4. He lives somewhere in the neighborhood. 他住在附近某处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('modify', '[\'mɑːdɪfaɪ]', 'v.修改；更改；缓和；修饰', '1. We have to modify our plan a little bit. 我们得对我们的计划稍加修改。 2. The policy was agreed by the committee, but only in a modified form. 那项政策经修改后才获得委员会同意。 3. The union has been forced to slightly modify its position. 工会被迫稍稍改变立场。 4. He\'ll have to modify his views if he wants to be elected. 他要想当选就得把观点改得缓和些。', '形容词: modifiable 名词: modifiability 过去式: modified 过去分词: modified 现在分词: modifying 第三人称单数: modifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('water', '[\'wɔːtər]', 'n.水；海域；雨水；海水 v.给 ... 浇水；给 ... 供水；加水稀释；充满眼泪；给...水喝', '1. The rain water drips from the roof. 雨水从屋顶滴下来。 2. I satisfied my thirst with a glass of water. 我喝了一杯水解渴。 3. Oceania is a separate landmass, but it is separated from Asia by very shallow water. 大洋洲是一块单独的陆地,但它与亚洲之间只隔着很浅的海域。 4. The rain water drips from the roof. 雨水从屋顶滴下来。 5. You can water the flowers every three days. 你可以每三天给花浇一次水。', '名词: waterer 过去式: watered 过去分词: watered 现在分词: watering 第三人称单数: waters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arithmetic', '[ə\'rɪθmətɪk]', 'n.算术；计算 adj.算术的', '1. I\'m good at history but not so hot at arithmetic. 我的历史成绩不错，但算术不太好。 2. He got the answer by mental arithmetic. 他用心算得出了答案。 3. My job is to instruct you in arithmetic. 我的工作就是指导你学算术。 4. I am not sure my arithmetic is correct, but I think the total is 75. 我不确定我的计算是不是正确,但是我认为总数是75。 5. I saw him puzzle over an arithmetic problem. 我看见他正在苦心思索一道算术题。', '形容词: arithmetical 副词: arithmetically 名词: arithmetician');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scale', '[skeɪl]', 'n.刻度；等级，规模；音阶；量程；天枰，磅秤；鳞片，鳞状物 v.攀登；按比例决定；称重；刮鳞；剥落', '1. How much does it read on the scale? 刻度显示的是多少? 2. The force of the wind is measured on a standard scale of 0-12. 风力是按0-12级标准等级测量的。 3. The fifth note of a scale is called a dominant. 音阶的第五音被称为属音。 4. It takes courage and strength to scale these cliffs. 攀登这些悬崖需要勇气和力量。', '形容词: scalelike 过去式: scaled 过去分词: scaled 现在分词: scaling 第三人称单数: scales');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('status', '[\'steɪtəs]', 'n.地位；情形；状况，状态；身份', '1. Women\'s social status has changed much over the years. 这些年来妇女的社会地位有了很大改变。 2. I\'ll keep you posted on the status. 我会随时告诉你进展的情形。 3. We ask the bank to report on his financial status. 我们请银行报告他的财政状况。 4. There are many fine shadings of status through the social hierarchy. 在各个社会等级之间有许多细微的身分区别。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('empire', '[\'empaɪər]', 'n.帝国；大企业；帝权', '1. He is the builder of the great empire. 他是大帝国的创立者。 2. The Roman Empire existed for several centuries. 罗马帝国存在了几百年。 3. Empire Qin is found in B.C. 221. 秦帝国建于公元前221年。 4. His business empire was truly vast. 他的企业规模极大.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('undergraduate', '[ˌʌndər\'ɡrædʒuət]', 'n.大学生 adj.大学生的；大学的', '1. A few years ago, sociology is the most popular subject for undergraduate. 几年之前，社会学是大学本科生最欢迎的课程。 2. He is a Harvard undergraduate. 他是哈佛大学的学生。 3. About half before New Year, some university psychology teachs the sexology questionnaire that ever sent me a concerned undergraduate. 大约半年前，某大学心理学教授曾送给我一份有关大学生的性学调查表。 4. Regressing to history original facts and cultivating undergraduate\'s interest of study is an important way that may improve teaching effects. 回归历史学科的本真，培养大学生的学习兴趣，是提高课堂教学效果的重要方式。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('analyse', '[\'ænəlaɪz]', 'vt.分析；细察', '1. He analysed the food and found that it contained poison. 他对这种食物做了化验，发现有毒。 2. Let\'s analyse the problem and see what went wrong. 让我们分析一下这道题，看什么地方出错了。 3. The coach tried to analyse the cause of our defeat. 教练努力设法分析我们失败的原因。 4. We must try to analyse the causes of the strike. 我们得研究一下罢工的原因。', '动词: analyze 形容词: analytic 副词: analytically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('characterize', '[\'kærəktəraɪz]', 'vt.表示 ... 的典型；赋予 ... 特色', '1. The novelist characterizes his heroine as capricious and passionate. 这位小说家把女主人公刻画成变化无常而又多情的人。 2. He may be characterized as a man of hobbies. 他可以被称作是一个有癖好的人。 3. Your work is characterized by lack of attention to details. 你的工作特点是缺乏对细节的注意。 4. Bold outlines and warm colors characterize his dominate style in painting. 他大胆的绘画和所有的暖色调表现了他独有的绘画特色。', '名词: characterizer 过去式: characterized 过去分词: characterized 现在分词: characterizing 第三人称单数: characterizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('watch', '[wɑːtʃ]', 'v.注视；看守；观看 n.手表；监视；看守；值班', '1. I seldom play chess, but I like to watch. 我很少下棋，但是喜欢看。 2. Watch what I do and how I do it. 注意看我的动作和方法。 3. I was assigned to watch the road. 我被派去护路。 4. We sat there watching basketball. 我们坐在那看篮球比赛。 5. How much is that watch? 那块手表多少钱?', '过去式: watched 过去分词: watched 现在分词: watching 第三人称单数: watches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('instruct', '[ɪn\'strʌkt]', 'v.教；命令；指导；[计] 指示', '1. His uncle instructed him in French. 他的叔叔教他法语。 2. Don\'t instruct your secretary to say you are out when you are in. 不要教你的秘书在你在的时候说不在。 3. It does not pertain to the young to instruct their elders. 年轻人不应该对老年人发号施令。 4. Please instruct me how to do my work. 请指导一下我如何工作。', '过去式: instructed 过去分词: instructed 现在分词: instructing 第三人称单数: instructs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cool', '[kuːl]', 'adj.凉爽的；凉的；冷静的；冷漠的 vt.(使)变凉；(使)冷却；(使)冷静 vi.变凉；冷静下来 n.凉爽；冷静；凉快 adv.冷静地', '1. A brisk walk in cool weather is invigorating. 在凉爽的天气里轻松地散步令人心旷神怡。 2. A cool breeze blew from the lake. 湖边吹来了一阵凉凉的微风。 3. As it was a hot day, she wore a cool dress. 因为天气热,她穿了一件凉快的衣服。 4. The occasion calls for a cool head. 在这样情况下需要有冷静的头脑。 5. Trees cool the air as well as clean it. 树木不仅能使空气变凉,而且能净化空气。 6. I\'m going into the woods to cool off. 我想进树林子里去凉快一下。 7. I like to feel the cool of the early morning. 我喜欢感受清晨的凉爽。 8. A real warrior can keep cool while fighting a strong enemy. 真正的勇士能沉着冷静地应对强大的敌人。', '形容词: coolish 副词: coolly 比较级: cooler 最高级: coolest 名词: coolness 过去式: cooled 过去分词: cooled 现在分词: cooling 第三人称单数: cools');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drip', '[drɪp]', 'n.滴；点滴；乏味的人 v.滴下；漏出', '1. A drip of water fell from the tap. 从龙头滴下一滴水。 2. The patient is on a drip. 病人正在输液。 3. The patient is put on a drip after her operation. 那个病人动过手术后就打点滴。 4. Don\'t be such a drip! Come and join in the fun. 别呆在那里了! 过来一起玩儿吧。 5. As water continues to drip, the icicle grows. 随着水不断下滴，冰柱的体积也慢慢增大。', '过去式: dripped 过去分词: dripped 现在分词: dripping 第三人称单数: drips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('understanding', '[ˌʌndər\'stændɪŋ]', 'n.理解；非正式协议；谅解；同情心 adj.有同情心的', '1. Love is the byname of understanding and care. 爱是理解和体贴的别名。 2. Such matters transcend human understanding. 这些事情是人类所无法理解的。 3. A knowledge of economics is fundamental to any understanding of this problem. 经济知识对于理解这个问题是至关重要的。 4. We have reached an understanding with them. 我们和他们达成了协议。', '副词: understandingly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heroine', '[\'heroʊɪn]', 'n.女英雄；女主角', '1. She became the heroine of France. 她成为法国的女英雄。 2. This story featured a plucky heroine. 这个故事描述了一个勇敢的女英雄。 3. I cannot believe she is the heroine of the movie. 我难以相信她是这部电影的女主角。 4. The heroine made her exit to great applause. 女主角在热烈的掌声中退场。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mill', '[mɪl]', 'n.磨坊；工厂；磨粉机 v.碾碎；磨；（使）乱转', '1. He sends his crop to a large mill instead of grinding it himself. 他把收获的庄稼送到大磨坊去，而不是自己碾磨。 2. The logs are drifted downstream to the mill. 那些原木沿河顺水漂到工厂。 3. Com is ground into flour in a mill. 谷物在磨粉机里磨成粉。 4. He used a miller to mill the grain into flour. 他用碾磨机把谷物磨成面粉。', '过去式: milled 过去分词: milled 现在分词: milling 第三人称单数: mills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('finger', '[\'fɪŋɡər]', 'n.指针；手指（尤指大拇指以外的手指） v.触碰；用指抚摸', '1. The finger of the clock points to twelve. 钟的指针指向十二点。 2. The pen slips out of my fingers. 钢笔从我指缝中滑下去了。 3. She poked her finger into the hole. 她把手指插入孔中。 4. She cut her finger on some broken glass. 她被碎玻璃划破了手指。 5. Please don\'t finger the goods. 请勿触摸这些物品。', '形容词: fingerless 名词: fingerer 过去式: fingered 过去分词: fingered 现在分词: fingering 第三人称单数: fingers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('movie', '[\'muːvi]', 'n.电影', '1. The movie was over shortly before six. 电影在六点钟不到就结束了。 2. The movie has been hyped up far beyond its worth. 这部影片被吹得离了谱了。 3. His last movie was a real turkey. 他最後的那部影片一塌糊涂。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('while', '[waɪl]', 'conj.当 ... 的时候；虽然；尽管；然而 n.一段时间；一会儿 v.消磨', '1. I lived in a hostel while I was a student. 我求学期间住在青年招待所里。 2. While Mary was writing a letter, the children were playing outside. 玛丽写信时，孩子们在外面玩耍。 3. In a word, while the prospects are bright, the road has twists and turns. 总之,虽然前途是光明的,但是道路是曲折的。 4. While I admit that there are problems, I don\'t agree that they cannot be solved. 尽管我承认有问题存在 5. I haven\'t seen him for a long while. 我已经很久没见到他了。 6. A detective story helps to while away the time. 侦探小说有助于打发时间。', '过去式: whiled 过去分词: whiled 现在分词: whiling 第三人称单数: whiles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('costume', '[\'kɑːstuːm]', 'n.服装；剧装 vt.提供服装；为 ... 设计服装 adj.服装打扮的', '1. This traditional costume is of indigo blue. 这件传统服装是靛蓝色的。 2. Her funny costume caused much mirthful laughter among the guests. 她那滑稽的服装引得客人哄堂大笑。 3. The kimono is part of the national costume of Japan. 和服是日本民族服装的一部分。 4. We patched up a costume for the play . 我们临时凑成了一件戏装。 5. Jane costumed a historical play. 简曾为一出历史剧设计服装。 6. A friend of mine was asked to a costume ball a short time ago. 不久前，我的一个朋友被邀请参加一个化装舞会。', '过去式: costumed 过去分词: costumed 现在分词: costuming 第三人称单数: costumes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reptile', '[\'reptaɪl]', 'n.爬行动物；卑鄙的人 adj.爬虫类的', '1. Snakes and crocodiles are reptiles. 蛇和鳄鱼都是爬行动物。 2. Strictly speaking,a slow-worm is a kind of reptile. 严格地说，蛇晰是一种爬行动物。 3. This creature can be subsumed in the class of reptile. 这种生物可以归入爬行动物一类. 4. The land is teeming with reptile life. 这片土地多爬行动物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fry', '[fraɪ]', 'v.油煎；油炸 n.<美>法式炸薯条', '1. The eggs are frying in the pan. 鸡蛋正在平底锅里煎着。 2. We cut it into thin slices and fry it. 我们把它切成薄片并用油煎。 3. Shall I fry the fish for dinner? 晚饭要不要我炸鱼？ 4. I will fry an onion to make onion rings. 我将炒一头洋葱，做炸葱圈。', '名词复数: fries 过去式: fried 过去分词: fried 现在分词: frying 第三人称单数: fries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('esteem', '[ɪ\'stiːm]', 'n.尊敬 vt.尊敬；认为', '1. We all have great esteem for you. 我们都非常敬重您。 2. All his students held him in high esteem. 他的学生对他都很尊敬。 3. No one can esteem you more than I do. 没有人会比我更敬重你。 4. He is esteemed for his courage. 他因有勇气而受人尊敬。', '过去式: esteemed 过去分词: esteemed 现在分词: esteeming 第三人称单数: esteems');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oblige', '[ə\'blaɪdʒ]', 'vt.迫使；责成；使感激；施恩于；帮 ... 的忙；使…成为必要 vi.帮忙', '1. The law oblige parents to send their children to school. 法律上要求父母送子女入学。 2. The Convention contains innovative measures that oblige countries to return stolen assets to their rightful owners. 公约载有一些责成各国将被盗资产返还其合法所有人的创新措施。 3. I\'m much obliged to you. 我非常感谢你。 4. I am obliged to you for your gracious hospitality. 我很感谢你的热情好客。 5. I\'ll do any thing within reason to oblige. 凡能做到的我都愿效劳。', '名词: obliger 过去式: obliged 过去分词: obliged 现在分词: obliging 第三人称单数: obliges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compliment', '[\'kɑːmplɪmənt]', 'n.称赞；恭维；(复数)致意 vt.恭维；称赞', '1. I was embarrassed by their compliment. 对他们的称赞我感到很不安。 2. I feel greatly flattered at your compliment. 我对你的称赞感到受宠若惊。 3. They paid him a high compliment. 他们非常恭维他。 4. My compliments to your wife. 向您的夫人致意。 5. He complimented her on her new dress without even looking at it. 他连看都没看一眼，就称颂她的新衣服。', '过去式: complimented 过去分词: complimented 现在分词: complimenting 第三人称单数: compliments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('press', '[pres]', 'v.按；压；逼迫；强迫服役；征用 n.新闻界；出版社；报刊；新闻舆论；压；熨烫机；印刷机', '1. Please press the controller to turn the machine on. 请按控制器来开机。 2. Press this button in case of fire. 遇火灾时按下此钮。 3. The book is crumpled and needs press. 书皱了需要压一压。 4. Press firmly on the wound to stop the bleeding. 用力压住伤口止血。 5. He denied that he had leaked the news to the press. 他否认曾将这则消息泄漏给新闻界。', '过去式: pressed 过去分词: pressed 现在分词: pressing 第三人称单数: presses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plural', '[\'plʊrəl]', 'adj.复数的 n.复数', '1. Most plural nouns in English end in s\'. 英语的复数名词多以s结尾。 2. We form the plural by the addition of \"es\". 我们通过加\"es\"构成该词的复数形式。', '副词: plurally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tennis', '[\'tenɪs]', 'n.网球', '1. Do you play tennis? 你打网球吗？ 2. I\'m just a rabbit at tennis. 我网球打得很差劲。 3. I won the tennis tournament. 我赢了那场网球比赛。 4. I want to buy a new tennis bat. 我想要买一个新网球拍。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('horrible', '[\'hɔːrəbl]', 'adj.可怕的；令人毛骨悚然的；令人讨厌的', '1. His heart sickened at the thought of that horrible scene. 他一想到那种可怕的情景就感到恶心。 2. Everything is in a horrible muddle. 一切都陷入可怕的混乱。 3. The sight of the battlefield was horrible. 战场的情景令人毛骨悚然。 4. Dense fog is always horrible to the driver. 对于路上的司机浓雾总是很讨厌的。', '副词: horribly 名词: horribleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dirt', '[dɜːrt]', 'n.污垢；泥土；灰尘', '1. He scoured off the dirt from the floor. 他擦去地板上的污垢。 2. Wash the dirt off your hands. 把你手上的泥污洗掉。 3. The dirt was deeply ground into the floor. 污垢被深深地压到地板里面去了。 4. The road petered out into a dirt track. 大道延伸到一条泥土小径。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('breeze', '[briːz]', 'n.微风；<口>轻而易举的事；焦炭渣 v.飘然而行；轻松通过', '1. The wheat rippled in the breeze. 小麦在微风中起伏波动。 2. We are enjoying the cool breeze that comes from the lake. 我们享受着湖面上吹来的凉爽微风。 3. We got the job done in a breeze. 我们轻而易举就把这件事办了。 4. Teaching you English is by no means a breeze. 教你英语绝对不是什么轻而易举的事。 5. She breezed along, smiling at everyone. 她轻盈地向前走去，对每个人都嫣然含笑。', '过去式: breezed 过去分词: breezed 现在分词: breezing 第三人称单数: breezes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('private', '[\'praɪvət]', 'adj.私人的；个人的；私下的；私有的；缄默的 n.士兵；列兵', '1. The president is paying a private visit to Europe. 总统正在欧洲进行私人访问。 2. We each have our private views about it. 我们每个人对这件事都有自己的看法。 3. The public is fascinated by the private lives of public figures. 公众对社会名流的私生活具有浓厚的兴趣。 4. Capitalism is based on private ownership. 资本主义是建立在私有制基础上的。 5. Dr.Kraemer,a former lawyer,was also a private in World WarⅠ. 克雷默博士以前当过律师,一战时也是个士兵。', '副词: privately 名词: privateness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('computer', '[kəm\'pjuːtər]', 'n.电脑；计算机', '1. I\'m getting a new computer for birthday present. 我得到一台电脑作生日礼物。 2. This computer company was established last year. 这家电脑公司是去年成立的。 3. In addition to giving a general introduction to computer, the course also provides practical experience. 课程除了一般介绍电脑知识外，还提供实际操作的机会。 4. I am a computer operator. 我是一名计算机操作人员。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prayer', '[prer]', 'n.祈祷；祷告；祷文；祈祷者', '1. She had a wakeful night spent in prayer. 她整夜祈祷。 2. The congregation in the church knelt in prayer. 教堂的会众跪下来祈祷。 3. I say my prayers every night before going to bed. 每天晚上上床前，我都要祈祷。 4. Her prayer answered and her son came home safely. 她的祈祷应验了，儿子平安地回到了家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('underestimate', '[ˌʌndər\'estɪmeɪt]', 'n.低估 v.低估', '1. The figure of $10 million was a serious underestimate. 一千万美元这个数据是一个严重的低估。 2. It seems to have been due to his consistent underestimate of her political weight. 看来是由于希思一贯低估她的政治能量。 3. Never underestimate the power of a woman. 决不要低估妇女的力量。 4. Don\'t underestimate the difficulties of the work. 不要低估了这项工作的艰巨性。', '名词: underestimation 过去式: underestimated 过去分词: underestimated 现在分词: underestimating 第三人称单数: underestimates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('naive', '[naɪ\'iːv]', 'adj.天真的；幼稚的', '1. He derides her naive attitude. 他嘲弄她天真的态度。 2. Children always ask naive questions. 小孩子总问天真的问题。 3. This theory was intended to deceive naive people. 这一理论旨在欺骗天真群众。 4. The politician made a naive decision. 这个政治家做了一个幼稚的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wrinkle', '[\'rɪŋkl]', 'n.皱纹；方法 vt.使起皱纹；皱着 vi.起皱', '1. She\'s beginning to get wrinkles round her eyes. 她的眼角开始有皱纹了。 2. My findings add a new wrinkle to each scenario. 我的发现为两种说法都提供了一点想法。 3. Too much sunbathing will wrinkle your skin. 皮肤晒得过分就能起皱纹。 4. He wrinkled up his forehead in perplexity. 他困惑地皱起了眉头。 5. The apples are beginning to wrinkle. 这些苹果开始起皱纹了。', '形容词: wrinkly 过去式: wrinkled 过去分词: wrinkled 现在分词: wrinkling 第三人称单数: wrinkles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('colleague', '[\'kɑːliːɡ]', 'n.同事', '1. Please allow me to introduce my colleague Professor Zhang to you. 请允许我把我的同事张教授介绍给你。', '名词: colleagueship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('found', '[faʊnd]', 'v.建立；创立；创办；熔铸；找到，发现（动词find的过去式和过去分词）', '1. This business company was founded in 1724. 这家商业公司建立于1724年。 2. A good relationship has to be founded on trust. 基于信任建立良好的关系。 3. They founded a college. 他们创办了一所大学。 4. Our goal is to found a lovely school. 我们的目标创办一所可爱的学校。', '过去式: founded 过去分词: founded 现在分词: founding 第三人称单数: founds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shelf', '[ʃelf]', 'n.架子；搁板；搁板状物 n.搁置；闲置', '1. He poised the glass on the shelf. 他把玻璃杯稳稳地放在架子上。 2. There were a lot of books on the shelves along the walls. 靠墙的书架上有许多书。 3. Please lift the box down from the shelf for me. 请帮我把这只箱子从搁板上抬下来。 4. I screwed up the jar and put it back on the shelf. 我把罐子拧上盖儿,放回搁架。 5. The plan has been put on a shelf since it\'s unrealistic. 鉴于其非现实性,该计划已被搁置。', '名词: shelfful 名词复数: shelves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('worry', '[\'wɜːri]', 'vt.撕咬；使烦恼；使焦虑 vi.担心；发愁 n.担心；烦恼；忧虑', '1. The dog was worrying a rat. 那条狗撕咬著一只老鼠。 2. Don\'t worry her; she is busy. 别去烦她，她很忙。 3. The noise doesn\'t seem to worry them. 这种嘈声好像并不影响他们。 4. What worries me is how he will manage now his wife\'s died. 他妻子死了 5. Don\'t worry if you can\'t finish it. 你做不完也不必担心。 6. Worry and illness had made him prematurely old. 他心事重重、 疾病缠身，落得个未老先衰。', '名词: worrier 名词复数: worries 过去式: worried 过去分词: worried 现在分词: worrying 第三人称单数: worries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suffer', '[\'sʌfər]', 'vt.遭受；忍受；容忍，宽恕，听任；允许，准许 vi.受苦；患病；受损失；变差，变糟；处于不利地位', '1. They suffered huge losses in the financial crisis. 他们在经济危机时遭受了巨大的损失。 2. She couldn\'t suffer criticism. 她受不了批评。 3. I can suffer your treachery, but not you incompetence. 我可以忍受你的背叛,但不能忍受你的无能。 4. How can you suffer such insolence? 你怎么能容忍这种蛮横的态度？ 5. I won\'t stand by and let him suffer like this. 我不会袖手旁观,让他这样受苦。', '副词: sufferingly 名词: sufferer 过去式: suffered 过去分词: suffered 现在分词: suffering 第三人称单数: suffers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rail', '[reɪl]', 'n.栏杆；扶手；铁轨 v.抱怨；责骂；以横木围栏；铺铁轨', '1. A towel hung from the rail. 栏杆上搭著条毛巾。 2. We installed a stainless steel towel rail on the wall. 我们在墙上装了一个不锈钢的挂毛巾的横杆。 3. Nobody believes that he can jump over that rail. 没人相信他能越过那个栏杆。 4. Hold on to the rail or you\'ll slip! 抓住扶手，不然你会滑倒的。 5. It is better to fight for good than to rail at the ill 与其抱怨,不如积善', '名词: railer 过去式: railed 过去分词: railed 现在分词: railing 第三人称单数: rails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('princess', '[ˌprɪn\'ses]', 'n.公主；王妃；贵妇；公爵夫人', '1. The magician transformed the frog into a princess. 魔术师把青蛙变成了公主。 2. The witch put the princess under a spell, and she fell asleep for ten years. 这女巫使公主中了巫术，沉睡了十年。 3. The kind dwarf asked the little princess to have dinner with him. 善良的小矮人邀请小公主和他一起吃晚饭。 4. She performs the duties of a princess with great aplomb. 她泰然自若地履行王妃的职责。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quantitative', '[\'kwɑːntəteɪtɪv]', 'adj.数量的；定量的', '1. He said it was only a quantitative difference. 他说这仅仅是数量上的差别。 2. Arms races have a quantitative and a qualitative aspects. 军备竞赛具有数量和质量两个方面。 3. We need to do a proper quantitative analysis of this problem. 我们需要对这个问题进行适当的定量分析。 4. The primary research method will be both qualitative and quantitative. 本文采用定性和定量相结合的研究方法。', '副词: quantitatively 名词: quantitativeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('laser', '[\'leɪzər]', 'n.激光；镭射', '1. Lasers can be used to perform operations nowadays. 现在激光可以用来做手术。 2. He monopolizes the laser printer. 他独占了这台激光打印机。 3. The doctor finished the operation, but his success depended on the backroom boys who had invented the new laser scalpel. 医生做完了手术，但他的成功有赖于那些发明了新型激光手术刀的研究人员。 4. A laser reflection will occur at each laminate substrate. 每一片玻璃都会产生一个镭射反射。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('choose', '[tʃuːz]', 'v.选择；决定', '1. It\'s up to you to choose where we should go. 我们要去的地点,由你负责选择。 2. He will choose banking as his career. 他将选择银行业做为职业。 3. He chose not to go home until later. 他决定晚一点才回家。', '名词: chooser 过去式: chose 过去分词: chosen 现在分词: choosing 第三人称单数: chooses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Monday', '[\'mʌndeɪ]', 'n.星期一', '1. He\'ll arrive on Monday. 他将于星期一到达。 2. Next Monday will be my 21st birthday. 下星期一是我二十一岁的生日。 3. The store took stock on Monday. 那家商店每逢星期一进行盘点。 4. The ship will start its maiden voyage next Monday. 这艘船将于下周一开始它的处女航。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chaos', '[\'keɪɑːs]', 'n.混乱；无秩序；混沌', '1. The wintry weather has caused chaos on the roads. 因风雪交加,道路上混乱不堪。 2. After the failure of the electricity supplies, the city was in chaos. 电力供应中断,城市陷于混乱之中。 3. Without rules, people would live in a state of chaos. 若无规则,人们将在混乱状态中生活。 4. Chaos often breeds life, when order breeds habit. 混沌常常孕育着生命，而秩序会产生习惯。', '形容词: chaotic 副词: chaotically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diagram', '[\'daɪəɡræm]', 'n.图解；图表 vt.用图解法表示', '1. She gave me a diagram of railway network. 她给了我一张铁路网图解。 2. The diagram had been copied with great precision. 该图表的复印件很精确。 3. He pointed at the diagram to illustrate his point. 他指着图表来说明他的论点。 4. He will diagram the entire procedure so that you can understand it more clearly. 他将把整个程序制成图表，这样你就会理解清楚了。', '形容词: diagrammable 副词: diagrammatically 过去式: diagrammed/diagramed 过去分词: diagrammed/diagramed 现在分词: diagramming/diagraming 第三人称单数: diagrams/diagrams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reclaim', '[rɪ\'kleɪm]', 'v.收回；回收；纠正；开垦', '1. After he stopped paying the hire purchase installment, the finance company tried to reclaim his car. 在他停止支付租购分期付款后，该金融公司试图收回他的汽车。 2. You may be entitled to reclaim some of the tax you paid last year. 你或许有权要求退回去年你交付的部分税金。 3. Their daily work is to reclaim rubber from old tyres. 他们的日常工作是用旧轮胎再生橡胶。 4. It is incumbent on me to reclaim him. 劝他改过是我义不容辞的义务。', '形容词: reclaimable 名词: reclaimant 过去式: reclaimed 过去分词: reclaimed 现在分词: reclaiming 第三人称单数: reclaims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mat', '[mæt]', 'n.垫子；席子 v.编织；集结；铺席于 ... 上', '1. There are some clods of soil on the mat. 垫子上有些土块。 2. He lifted the mat and slid the key under (it). 他掀起垫子把钥匙悄悄放在下面。 3. I wiped my shoes on the mat before I came in. 我在进门前把鞋在垫子上擦了擦。 4. Scrape your shoes on the door mat before you come in. 进屋前先在门口擦鞋垫上擦一擦鞋子。 5. The swimmer\'s wet hair was matted together. 那游泳者的湿头发乱糟糟结成一团。', '过去式: matted 过去分词: matted 现在分词: matting 第三人称单数: mats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('add', '[æd]', 'v.加；增加；补充', '1. If you add 4 to 5, you get 9. 四加五等于九。 2. If the tea is too strong, add some hot water to it. 如果茶太浓,加点开水。 3. He added some wood to increase the fire. 他加了一些木柴，使火旺些。 4. He did nothing but add to our trouble. 他什么也没做,只是增加了我们的麻烦。', '形容词: addable 过去式: added 过去分词: added 现在分词: adding 第三人称单数: adds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expert', '[\'ekspɜːrt]', 'n.专家；能手 adj.熟练的；内行的', '1. She is a reputable expert. 她是个有声望的专家。 2. According to expert opinions, they gave up the experiment immediately. 根据专家们的意见，他们马上放弃了这项试验。 3. He is an expert in unarmed combat. 他是徒手格斗的能手。 4. The surgeon cut away the tumour with expert skill. 外科大夫用熟练的技术把肿瘤切去。', '副词: expertly 名词: expertness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('section', '[\'sekʃn]', 'n.部分；部门；章节；区域；断面；剖面图；零件；路段；切开 v.划分；切开', '1. White lines divide the playing area into sections. 这些白线把赛区分成各个部分。 2. I hope someone competent will join our section. 我希望有能力的人加入本部门。 3. The report has a section on accidents at work. 报告中有一段谈到工作中的事故问题。 4. She lives near the business section. 她住在商业区附近。', '过去式: sectioned 过去分词: sectioned 现在分词: sectioning 第三人称单数: sections');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exemplify', '[ɪɡ\'zemplɪfaɪ]', 'vt.例证；示范', '1. I will exemplify my point with a story. 我会用一个故事举例说明我的观点。 2. To exemplify this theory,let us examine some species of insect. 为举例说明这种理论，我们来检查一些种类的昆虫。 3. The plays of Wilds exemplify the comedy of manners. 王尔德的戏剧是风尚喜剧的典范。 4. The recent oil price rises exemplify the difficulties which the motor industry is now facing. 最近的石油涨价是汽车工业正面临的困难的一个例子。', '形容词: exemplifiable 名词: exemplifier 过去式: exemplified 过去分词: exemplified 现在分词: exemplifying 第三人称单数: exemplifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impart', '[ɪm\'pɑːrt]', 'vt.传授；赋予；告知', '1. A teacher\'s aim is to impart knowledge. 教师的作用是传授知识。 2. They had come to impart their experience in stock raising. 他们是来传授饲养牲畜的经验的。 3. The red curtains impart a certain elegance to the room. 红色的窗帘使房间平添几分雅致。 4. Your presence will impart an air of elegance to the party. 您的光临将会为宴会增添优雅的气氛。', '过去式: imparted 过去分词: imparted 现在分词: imparting 第三人称单数: imparts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extraordinary', '[ɪk\'strɔːrdəneri]', 'adj.非凡的；特别的；特派的', '1. He has an extraordinary memory. 他有非凡的记忆力。 2. His extraordinary skill was praised by all. 他超凡的技艺博得了广泛的赞誉。 3. I find it very extraordinary. 我觉得这非常离奇。 4. He is full of extraordinary ideas. 他满脑子都是离奇的想法。', '副词: extraordinarily');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('later', '[\'leɪtər]', 'adv.后来；稍后 adj.后来的；以后的；接近末期的', '1. She had her baby weaned a year later. 她在一年后才把孩子的奶断掉。 2. I\'ll speak with her later. 我要稍后跟她谈。 3. I can\'t pay now, please bill me later. 我现在不能付款，请以后开帐单给我。 4. Later information showed that the sub did sink. 后来的情报显示潜艇确实被击沉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('zone', '[zoʊn]', 'n.地域；地带；地区', '1. They are pulling their troops out of the battle zone. 他们正把部队调离战区。 2. They have declared their country a, nuclear-free zone. 他们宣布本国为无核区。 3. Most of China is in the temperate zone. 中国的大部分地区在温带。 4. Some people live in Torrid Zone. 有些人生活在热带。', '过去式: zoned 过去分词: zoned 现在分词: zoning 第三人称单数: zones');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('amount', '[ə\'maʊnt]', 'n.数量；总额 vi.总计；等于', '1. A petrol gauge shows the amount of petrol left in a car. 汽油表指示出汽车里所剩的汽油数量。 2. He has a large amount of mail to answer every day. 他每天有大量的信件要回复。 3. Remember to tell the guest the amount of the bill. 记得告诉客人帐单的总额。 4. We charge one percent commission on the total amount. 我们收取支票总额的1%25作为手续费。 5. The total cost of repairs amounted to 100 dollars. 修理费用总计一百美元。', '过去式: amounted 过去分词: amounted 现在分词: amounting 第三人称单数: amounts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rule', '[ruːl]', 'n.规则；条例；习惯；统治；直尺 v.支配；统治；画直线', '1. Can you explain the thirty-second rule to me? 可以给我解释一下30秒规则吗? 2. It\'s against the rule to pick up the ball. 捡球是犯规的。 3. Is this rule in operation yet? 这一条例生效了吗? 4. I make it a rule to take a short walk after lunch. 我习惯在午饭后散散步。 5. I am slowly but surely going to rule this land. 我一定会慢慢地统一这片土地。', '形容词: rulable 过去式: ruled 过去分词: ruled 现在分词: ruling 第三人称单数: rules');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('practically', '[\'præktɪkli]', 'adv.实际上；几乎；简直', '1. Bread was practically non-existent. 实际上没有面包。 2. Practically, the plan didn\'t work well. 实际上该计划进行得不顺利。 3. He is practically ruined. 他几乎破产了。 4. The town was practically deserted. 该镇几乎已空无一人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('southwest', '[ˌsaʊθ\'west]', 'n.西南；西南风；西南地区 adj.西南的；来自西南方的 adv.往西南；来自西南', '1. Wales is in the southwest of the British Island. 威尔士在大不列颠岛的西南部。 2. Plentiful rainfall is expected in Southwest China. 中国西南地区会出现明显降水。 3. Tainan is situated in the southwest part of Taiwan not far from Kaohsiung. 台南位于台湾的西南方，在离高雄不远处。 4. This river flowed southwest to the Atlantic Ocean. 这条河流向西南，汇入大西洋。', '形容词: southwestern');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('civilian', '[sə\'vɪljən]', 'adj.平民的 n.罗马法专家；平民', '1. He resigned his commission to take up a civilian job. 他辞去军职而从事平民工作。 2. People are indignant by their shooting of innocent civilians. 对于他们枪杀无辜平民，人们感到义愤填膺。 3. A civilian was killed by a stray bullet. 一个平民被流弹打死。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('imitation', '[ˌɪmɪ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.模仿；效法 adj.假造的；冒充的', '1. Young children learn how to speak by imitation. 儿童通过模仿学说话。 2. He grew beards in imitation of the actor. 他为了模仿那个演员,蓄起了胡子。 3. His style is a slavish imitation of his teacher\'s. 他一味模仿教师的风格，毫无创意。 4. Her innocence is only an imitation. 她的天真只是一种伪装。', '形容词: imitational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('treaty', '[\'triːti]', 'n.条约；协定', '1. The treaty gave (a) fresh impetus to trade. 这条约使双方的贸易又推进了一步。 2. There is a contentious clause in the treaty. 这条约中有一条有争议的条款。 3. The Government has signed a treaty with Moscow. 政府已与莫斯科签了一项条约。 4. The house was sold by private treaty. 这所房子以私人协议的方式售出。', '名词复数: treaties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conform', '[kən\'fɔːrm]', 'v.使一致；遵从', '1. His ideas do not conform to mine. 他的想法和我的不一致。 2. He doesn\'t conform to the usual stereotype of the city businessman with a dark suit and rolled umbrella. 他不像典型的城市商人那样，穿一身深色的套服、 带一把收好的雨伞。 3. She refused to conform to the normal social conventions. 她拒绝遵从正常的社会习俗。 4. She left home to escape the pressure to conform to her family\'s way of life. 她离家出走以求摆脱她家生活方式对她的束缚。', '名词: conformer 过去式: conformed 过去分词: conformed 现在分词: conforming 第三人称单数: conforms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('span', '[spæn]', 'n.时期；跨度；间距 vt.延续；横跨；贯穿；遍及；弥补 动词spin的过去式形式.', '1. Modern medicine has increased man\'s life span. 现代医学延长了人的寿命。 2. He has settled here for a long span of time. 他已经在这儿定居很长一段时间了。 3. The arch has a span of 60 meters. 拱门的跨度为60米。 4. The spider has a leg span of 3 inches. 这个蜘蛛的腿的长度为3英寸。 5. The shipwrecks span nearly a century. 这些船只残骸已有近百年历史。', '过去式: spanned 过去分词: spanned 现在分词: spanning 第三人称单数: spans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ponder', '[\'pɑːndər]', 'v.沉思；考虑', '1. You should pause and ponder now. 你现在应该停下来仔细考虑一下。 2. He pondered long and deeply over the question. 他对该问题作了长时间的深思。 3. We pondered whether to tell her. 我们考虑是否要告诉她。 4. He pondered for some minutes before giving an answer. 他思考了几分钟才作答复。', '名词: ponderer 过去式: pondered 过去分词: pondered 现在分词: pondering 第三人称单数: ponders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('criticize', '[\'krɪtɪsaɪz]', 'v.批评；挑剔；评论；非难；吹毛求疵', '1. You should not criticize him so harshly in his face. 你不应该当面这么严厉地批评他。 2. Basicly there is nothing to criticize in his works. 他的作品基本上无可挑剔。 3. Would you like to read and criticize my new novel? 您愿意阅读并评论一下我的新小说吗? 4. He is too ready to criticize others. 他很喜欢评论别人。', '形容词: criticizable 名词: criticizer 过去式: criticized 过去分词: criticized 现在分词: criticizing 第三人称单数: criticizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scare', '[sker]', 'v.受惊吓；恐吓；吓走 n.惊吓；惊恐', '1. You scare them to death with your mouth. 你一开口就能把人吓死。 2. We\'ll scare her out of telling the police. 我们要把她吓得不敢报警。 3. His threats scared them out of carrying out the plan. 他的威胁迫使他们不敢实行该计划。 4. The dog scared the thief away. 狗把小偷吓走了。 5. You did give me a scare. 你真吓了我一跳。', '名词: scarer 过去式: scared 过去分词: scared 现在分词: scaring 第三人称单数: scares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tame', '[teɪm]', 'adj.驯服的；柔顺的；乏味的 vt.驯养；使驯服；压制 vi.变得驯服', '1. A boy was playing with a tame snake. 一个男孩在玩一条驯服了的蛇。 2. The animals we find in the zoo are quite tame. 我们在动物园看到的动物都很驯服。 3. It\'s incredible that the tame wolf is as mild as a lamb. 令人难以置信的是驯服的狼温和如羊。 4. She is too tame. 她太柔顺了。 5. The Asian elephant can be tamed and trained. 亚洲象可以被驯养和训练。 6. That tiger is impossible to tame. 那只老虎难以驯服。', '形容词: tamable 副词: tamely 比较级: tamer 最高级: tamest 名词: tameness 过去式: tamed 过去分词: tamed 现在分词: taming 第三人称单数: tames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reform', '[rɪ\'fɔːrm]', 'n.改革；改良 v.改革；革新；改造', '1. Our reform made an inexorable march of progress. 我们的改革取得了势不可挡的进展。 2. Many reforms must be made to the education system. 教育体制要作许多改革。 3. The reform and open policy has Brought us Chinese people a rich and colourful life. 改革开放的政策给我们中国人民带来了富裕和多彩的生活。 4. He intends to make several reforms in the prison system. 他打算在监狱制度方面实行一些改良。 5. A new leader will reform the unjust system. 新的领导人将改革不当的制度。', '形容词: reformable 名词: reformability 过去式: reformed 过去分词: reformed 现在分词: reforming 第三人称单数: reforms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deserve', '[dɪ\'zɜːrv]', 'vt.应受；值得', '1. He has done nothing to deserve death. 他没做过该受死刑的事。 2. You deserve a reward for being so helpful. 你帮了这么大的忙，理应受到奖励。 3. These proposals deserve careful study. 这些建议值得认真研究。', '过去式: deserved 过去分词: deserved 现在分词: deserving 第三人称单数: deserves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('magic', '[\'mædʒɪk]', 'n.魔法；魔术；魔力 adj.有魔力的；魔术的；奇妙的', '1. The fairy\'s magic changed the two brothers into swans. 仙子用魔法将两兄弟变成了天鹅。 2. Some people still believe in magic. 有些人仍然相信魔法。 3. True magic is a very subtle thing. 真正的魔法是一种非常微妙的事。 4. The paper turned green as if by magic. 这纸魔术般地变成了绿色。 5. The witch put a magic spell on the prince and turned him into a frog. 巫师向王子施了具有魔力的咒语,把他变成了一只青蛙。', '过去式: magicked 过去分词: magicked 现在分词: magicking 第三人称单数: magics');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('near', '[nɪr]', 'adj.近的；近似的；亲近的；吝啬的 adv.在附近；不久以后；几乎；[罕]吝啬地 prep.附近；接近；临近；大约；(质量、大小等)相仿；濒临 v.接近；靠近', '1. His flat\'s very near. 他的公寓就在附近。 2. We will meet in Beijing in the near future. 在不久的将来，我们将在北京见面。 3. The supermarket is very near to the station. 超级市场离车站很近。 4. Can you tell me the nearest way to the railway station? 你能告诉我去火车站最近的路吗？ 5. I found some shops quite near. 我发现附近有几个商店。 6. His clinic is near the newly-built railway station. 他的诊所在新建的火车站附近。 7. He must be nearing home by now. 他现在一定已经快到家了。', '比较级: nearer 最高级: nearest 名词: nearness 过去式: neared 过去分词: neared 现在分词: nearing 第三人称单数: nears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('claim', '[kleɪm]', 'n.要求；要求权；主张；断言；声称；要求物 vt.要求；请求；主张；声称；断言', '1. The matter claimed our serious attention. 这件事需要我们认真注意。 2. Did you claim on the insurance after your car accident? 出了车祸后，你向保险公司要求赔偿了吗？ 3. The government would not even consider his claim for money. 政府甚至不考虑他的赔款要求。 4. He set up a claim to the throne. 他自称王位是属于他的。', '形容词: claimable 名词: claimer 过去式: claimed 过去分词: claimed 现在分词: claiming 第三人称单数: claims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ending', '[\'endɪŋ]', 'n.结尾；结局', '1. The story is flawed by a weak ending. 这个故事因结尾写得马虎而显得逊色了。 2. Write your own ending dear reader. 亲爱的读者，您自己来作一个结尾吧。 3. The writer contrived a happy ending. 作者安排了一个大团圆的结局。 4. She got revved up by the tragic ending of the film. 她为这部电影的悲惨结局激动不已。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('depress', '[dɪ\'pres]', 'vt.使沮丧；压下；使萧条；降低；压抑', '1. He was depressed by his defeat. 失败让他沮丧。 2. The thought of having to take the exam again depressed me. 想到还需重新考试，我就感到沮丧。 3. The rainy days always depress me. 雨天总是使我沮丧。 4. Depress this button to rewind the tape. 按下这个按钮倒带。', '形容词: depressible 过去式: depressed 过去分词: depressed 现在分词: depressing 第三人称单数: depresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deviate', '[\'diːvieɪt]', 'v.偏离；脱离 n.叛离者；偏差；不正常的人或物 adj.离经叛道的', '1. Don\'t always deviate to minor issues. 不要老是偏离到次要问题上去。 2. You will not deviate from your present course. 你不能偏离目前航线 3. His remarks usually deviate from truth. 他的话通常都与事实不符。 4. Do not deviate from the beaten track. 不要逸出常轨。', '形容词: deviatory 名词: deviator 过去式: deviated 过去分词: deviated 现在分词: deviating 第三人称单数: deviates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('address', '[ə\'dres]', 'n.住址；网址；电子邮箱地址；称呼；致词；讲话；演讲；谈吐 v.称呼；发表演说；提出；写地址；处理', '1. Please write your home address on the registration form. 请在这张登记表上写下你的家庭住址。 2. I\'ll log in to the internet to know about you. I know your address. 我还是上因特网去看吧，我知道你们的网址。 3. Can you tell me your E-mail address? 能告诉我你的电子邮箱地址吗? 4. What form of address should one use when writing to a bishop? 给主教写信应该怎样称呼? 5. Most people call me Bob. How do I address you? 大家叫我鲍勃,我怎么称呼你?', '过去式: addressed 过去分词: addressed 现在分词: addressing 第三人称单数: addresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sailor', '[\'seɪlər]', 'n.海员；水手；扁平的硬边草帽', '1. He went about in the disguise of a sailor. 他伪装成海员到处流窜。 2. The sailor was rated as an ordinary seaman. 那个水手被列为普通海员。 3. A sailor is at the mercy of the weather. 水手受到天气的摆布。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chop', '[tʃɑːp]', 'v.劈；砍；剁 n.砍；剁；排骨', '1. He chopped in with a sarcastic remark. 他突然插进一句讽刺的话。 2. She chopped the block of wood in two with a single blow. 她一斧头把木块劈成两半。 3. We had to chop a way through the undergrowth. 我们必须在矮树林中劈出一条路来。 4. You\'ve got to chop up the pork before stewing it. 你必须把猪肉剁细后再炖。 5. The hunter cut off the animal\'s head with one chop of an ax. 猎人一斧砍下猎物的头。', '过去式: chopped 过去分词: chopped 现在分词: chopping 第三人称单数: chops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('frost', '[frɔːst]', 'n.霜；霜冻；严寒 v.结霜；冻死；用糖衣装饰', '1. The windscreen was covered with frost. 挡风玻璃上结了霜。 2. Sweet potatoes decayed after the frost. 霜下了之后,地瓜烂掉了。 3. The crops were blasted by frost. 农作物被霜冻毁了。 4. Frost caused the split in the rock. 霜冻使岩石裂了一条缝。 5. The cold has frosted the windows. 寒冷的天气使窗子上结满了霜。', '过去式: frosted 过去分词: frosted 现在分词: frosting 第三人称单数: frosts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('royalty', '[\'rɔɪəlti]', 'n.皇家；皇族 n.版税', '1. She claims to be descended from royalty. 她声称她是皇室后裔。 2. Salt was an important item on the table of royalty. 盐在皇家餐桌上占有重要的位置。 3. This palace was home to French royalty. 这座宫殿是法国皇族的住宅。 4. His income is mainly from royalty. 他的收入主要来自版税。', '名词复数: royalties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cherry', '[\'tʃeri]', 'n.樱桃；樱桃树；樱桃色；<俚>处女膜', '1. He went to the cherry orchard to see flowers. 他去樱桃园看花。 2. We have different pies, such as apple, cherry, and strawberry pies. 我们有不同的派，例如苹果、樱桃和草莓派。 3. Cherry trees flower in the early spring. 樱桃树在早春开花。 4. She needs a cherry cabinet in her room. 她需要在她房里添一个樱桃木的柜子。', '名词复数: cherries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('increasingly', '[ɪn\'kriːsɪŋli]', 'adv.逐渐地；越来越多地', '1. Increasingly, farm land is yielding to property development. 地产的发展逐渐占据了农田。 2. New Zealand is an increasingly multicultural society. 新西兰已经逐渐成为多元文化交融的国家。 3. He grew increasingly to rely on her. 他越来越依赖她了。 4. Common preconceptions about life in this district are increasingly being challenged. 原先普遍存在著对那一地区生活的成见越来越站不住脚了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('house', '[haʊs]', 'n.房屋；住一屋的人；机构；议院；观众；听众；黄道十二宫之一 v.给…房子住；储存(某物)；容纳；藏有', '1. Her house is furnished in excellent taste. 她的房屋布置得非常高雅。 2. They are going to move to a new house next week. 下星期他们将迁入新居。 3. My dream is to have a big house among peach trees. 我的梦想就是在桃林间拥有一座大房子。 4. Be quiet or you\'ll wake the whole house! 安静点吧，别把全家人都吵醒了！ 5. He tried to feed and house his family. 他设法为一家人解决吃和住的问题。', '名词复数: houses 过去式: housed 过去分词: housed 现在分词: housing 第三人称单数: houses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cave', '[keɪv]', 'n.洞穴；山洞 v.挖空；塌落；屈服', '1. This cave was used by smugglersin the eighteenth century. 这个洞穴是十八世纪走私的人使用的。 2. The cliffs are riddled with caves. 岩壁上布满洞穴。 3. We kindled a firebrand in the cave. 我们在山洞里点燃火把。 4. The boys huddled together in the cave to keep warm. 男孩子们在山洞里挤成一团取暖。 5. The roof of the old house caved in. 那栋旧房子的屋顶塌下了。', '名词: caver 过去式: caved 过去分词: caved 现在分词: caving 第三人称单数: caves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conceal', '[kən\'siːl]', 'vt.隐藏；隐瞒；掩盖', '1. He concealed himself behind the tree. 他藏在树后。 2. It is against law to conceal evidence. 隐藏证据是违法的。 3. It is wrong for a man to conceal things from his wife. 一个男人对妻子隐瞒事情是不对的。 4. She tried to conceal what she had done to them. 她试图隐瞒对他们所做的事。', '形容词: concealable 名词: concealer 过去式: concealed 过去分词: concealed 现在分词: concealing 第三人称单数: conceals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brandy', '[\'brændi]', 'n.白兰地酒 v.以白兰地酒调制', '1. She fainted but the brandy soon revived her. 她昏迷了，但喂她些白兰地酒就很快醒过来了。 2. I drank a miniature bottle of brandy last night. 我昨晚喝了一小瓶白兰地。 3. John kept swigging at the bottle of brandy. 约翰对着那瓶白兰地酒大口地喝个不停。', '名词复数: brandies 过去式: brandied 过去分词: brandied 现在分词: brandying 第三人称单数: brandies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assault', '[ə\'sɔːlt]', 'n.攻击；突袭；抨击 vt.袭击；突袭', '1. Trainee commandos are put through an exhausting assault course. 受训的突击队员要参加令人筋疲力尽的突击课程。 2. The court determined that the man was guilty of assault. 法庭裁定那个人犯了侵犯人身罪。 3. A deep, wide ditch, usually filled with water, typically surrounding a fortified medieval town, fortress, or castle as a protection against assault. 护城河一条深而宽的、通常有水沟环绕设防的中世纪城镇城堡或堡垒，用以抵抗外来袭击 4. The article was a vicious assault on Bell\'s integrity. 这篇文章是对贝尔完整性的恶劣抨击。 5. Six women have been sexually assaulted in the area recently. 最近这一带有六个女子遭受强奸猥亵。', '名词: assaulter 过去式: assaulted 过去分词: assaulted 现在分词: assaulting 第三人称单数: assaults');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plight', '[plaɪt]', 'n.困境；苦境 n.誓约 vt.宣誓；订婚', '1. The Government seems to be closing its eyes to the plight of the unemployed. 政府似乎对失业者的困境熟视无睹。 2. The television pictures brought home to us all the plight of the refugees. 我们从电视上知道了难民所处的一切困境。 3. The plight of the refugees really wrung my heart. 难民处境惨苦真叫我牵肠割肚。 4. The plight of the refugees arouses the compassionate old man. 难民的困苦唤醒了那位有同情心的老人。 5. I plight that I will always be faithful to my work. 我发誓我会一直忠诚于我的工作。', '名词: plighter 过去式: plighted 过去分词: plighted 现在分词: plighting 第三人称单数: plights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('single', '[\'sɪŋɡl]', 'adj.单一的；单个的；特指某人或某物；单身的；单人的；单程的 n.单程票；单曲；单人房间；单身者；<美>一元纸币；(网球)单打比赛；(板球)一分打；(棒球)一垒打 v.挑选(一个)', '1. The letter was written on a single sheet of paper. 这封信只用一张纸写成。 2. I\'d like to have a single room, preferably, facing south. 我想要一个套间,最好是朝南的。 3. Every single child will receive a gift. 每一个孩子都会收到一份礼物 4. Freshwater is the single most precious element for life on earth. 淡水对地球上的生命来说是最宝贵的一个要素。 5. There are two second-class singles to Leeds. 有两张到利兹的二等的单程票. 6. The teacher was reluctant to single out individual students for praise or blame. 老师不愿挑出个别学生来给予表扬或者指责。', '名词: singleness 过去式: singled 过去分词: singled 现在分词: singling 第三人称单数: singles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('portray', '[pɔːr\'treɪ]', 'vt.描写；描绘；饰演', '1. It is difficult to portray feelings in words. 感情很难用言语来描写。 2. The book portrays the life of an actor. 这本书描述了一个演员的一生。 3. The picture portrays a beautiful sunset. 这幅画描绘了落日美景。 4. The actor is trying his best to portray the role of Hamlet. 这位演员尽力扮演哈姆雷特的角色。', '形容词: portrayable 名词: portrayer 过去式: portrayed 过去分词: portrayed 现在分词: portraying 第三人称单数: portrays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('equip', '[ɪ\'kwɪp]', 'vt.装备；具备；准备；穿 abbr.装备（=equipment）', '1. They can\'t afford to equip their army. 他们无力装备自己的军队。 2. We must equip the army for the modern war. 我们必须装备军队打现代化战争。 3. He is equipped with much experience in teaching. 他具有丰富的教学经验。 4. Could you help me equip the caravan? 你能帮我准备好这辆旅行车上的装备吗?', '过去式: equipped 过去分词: equipped 现在分词: equipping 第三人称单数: equips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('voice', '[vɔɪs]', 'n.声音；嗓音；[语]语态；发言权；意见 vt.表达；[语]发音；[音]调音', '1. His voice shook with fear. 他害怕得声音发抖。 2. The little girl spoke in a high childish voice. 小女孩说话时声音尖尖的，带着童音。 3. We could hear the children\'s voices in the garden. 我们可以听到花园里孩子们的声音。 4. She is enamored of the sound of her own voice. 她陶醉于自己的嗓音。 5. He was chosen to voice their grievance. 他被选去表达他们的不满。', '过去式: voiced 过去分词: voiced 现在分词: voicing 第三人称单数: voices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('voluntary', '[\'vɑːlənteri]', 'adj.自愿的；志愿的 n.(教堂礼拜仪式前后或进行期间的)乐器独奏', '1. He made a voluntary statement to the police. 他自愿为警方作供。 2. Many social services are still provided by voluntary societies in our city. 在我们的城市，许多社会服务仍然是有志愿团体提供的。 3. We rely entirely on voluntary contribution. 我们全靠自愿捐赠。 4. She\'s very taken up with voluntary work at the moment. 她目前大部分时间和精力都用在志愿工作上了。', '副词: voluntarily 名词: voluntariness 名词复数: voluntaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('superfluous', '[suː\'pɜːrfluəs]', 'adj.多余的；过剩的；不必要的', '1. Repack all the superfluous cups in the box. 把多余的杯子都重新装入箱中。 2. He has already been told, so our comments are superfluous. 早就有人同他说过，所以我们的意见是多余的。 3. The market is already superfluous. 市场已经过剩了。 4. She crossed out all the superfluous words and phrases in the draft. 她把草稿中不必要的词句都杠掉了。', '副词: superfluously 名词: superfluousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('camp', '[kæmp]', 'n.野营；帐篷；营地 v.宿营；露营；扎营', '1. We\'re going to have a sports camp in the countryside during our summer vacation. 暑假期间我们要在乡下搞一次运动野营。 2. They spent the summer in a camp in the mountains. 他们在山中野营度过夏天。 3. The travellers set up a camp near the river. 旅游者在河边架起了帐篷。 4. They pitched camp on the moor for the night. 他们在高沼地搭帐篷过夜。 5. We like to camp on the flats near the lake. 我们想要在湖边的平地上宿营。', '形容词: campy 过去式: camped 过去分词: camped 现在分词: camping 第三人称单数: camps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('opponent', '[ə\'poʊnənt]', 'n.对手；反对者；敌手 adj.反对的；敌对的', '1. He was assailed by his political opponent. 他遭到政敌的攻击。 2. I tried to comfort him after he was defeated by his opponent. 他被对手击败后，我尽力安慰他。 3. He knocked down his opponent with a powerful left. 他一记有力的左手拳将对手击倒。 4. He is slashing wildly at his opponent with a sword. 他正用剑疯狂地朝对手乱砍。 5. The company, which had long been an opponent of electrification, changed its stance earlier this year in light of slipping global sales. 该公司长期以来一直反对的电气化，改变了其立场，在今年早些时候，鉴于全球销售下滑。', '名词: opponency');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('incidence', '[\'ɪnsɪdəns]', 'n.发生(率)；入射', '1. Each incidence of truancy will impact the citizenship credit. 每次发生玩忽职守事件都会影响公民的信用。 2. Basically, can effectively control the incidence of bird strike. 基本上可以有效控制鸟击事件的发生。 3. Then I have to think deeply what benefit there is behind the incidence. 那时候我就必须深思发生的事情背后有什么益处。 4. he measured the angle of incidence of the reflected light. 他仔细测量了光的入射的角度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('statesman', '[\'steɪtsmən]', 'n.政治家', '1. The statesman is respected by people. 这位政治家为人们所敬重。 2. He will go down in history as a great statesman. 他将作为伟大的政治家而载入史册。', '形容词: statesmanlike 名词: statesmanship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('doll', '[dɑːl]', 'n.玩具娃娃；美貌女子；有吸引力的人 v.打扮', '1. My daughter has many beautiful dolls. 我女儿有许多漂亮的洋娃娃。 2. She wanted very much a doll for Christmas. 她非常想要一个玩具娃娃作为圣诞节的礼物。 3. My grand-daughter is a little doll. 我的孙女是个小可人儿。 4. Hence with the alternating operation of the inflator the doll is raised or lowered to achieve an attractive effect. 因此，与交替运作的充气，娃娃是提高或降低要达到一个具吸引力的效果。 5. She was all dolled up in furs and jewels. 她以皮大衣和珠宝把自己打扮得漂漂亮亮。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interrupt', '[ˌɪntə\'rʌpt]', 'v.打断；打扰；中断；阻碍 n.[计算机]中断', '1. It\'s not polite to interrupt a speaker. 打断人的谈话是不礼貌的。 2. The sudden noise from the next room interrupted my train of thinking. 从隔壁房间突然传来的吵闹声打断了我的思路。 3. I must go on, so please don\'t interrupt me. 我必须做下去,请不要打扰我。 4. Excuse me, I wonder if I could interrupt you for a moment. 对不起,能不能打扰您一会儿? 5. When I nod my head, that\'s your cue to interrupt the meeting. 我一点头，就是暗示你把会议中断。', '形容词: interruptible 名词: interruption 过去式: interrupted 过去分词: interrupted 现在分词: interrupting 第三人称单数: interrupts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cite', '[saɪt]', 'vt.引用；传讯；表扬；举(例)', '1. The lawyer cited a previous case to support his argument. 律师引用了以前的案例来支持他的论点。 2. It\'s no use citing the Bible to somebody who doesn\'t believe in God. 对不信上帝的人引用圣经的话是没用的。 3. I\'ll just cite some figures for comparison. 我要引用一些数字作比较。 4. He was cited for contempt of court. 他因蔑视法庭而被传讯。', '形容词: citable 过去式: cited 过去分词: cited 现在分词: citing 第三人称单数: cites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('salary', '[\'sæləri]', 'n.薪水 v.给 ... 薪水', '1. His money comes mainly from salary. 他的钱主要来自工资。 2. I want to speak to her in the matter of my salary. 我想跟她谈谈我的薪水问题。 3. Don\'t worry about him, he will be salaried by a big company. 别为他担心,一家大公司会给他发薪水。 4. Like those who work for government or nonprofit organizations, they are salaried rather than paid a fee. 同在政府或非盈利性组织工作的会计师一样，他们是挣工薪而不是按每笔业务收费。', '形容词: salaried 名词复数: salaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('being', '[\'biːɪŋ]', 'n.存在；人；生物；本质', '1. I don\'t like being pent up in the house all the time. 我不喜欢整天给关在屋子里。 2. It is fun eating by stealth without being found. 偷吃而不被人发现很有趣。 3. Earthenware has an advantage over wood in being more easily kept clean. 陶器的优点在于比木器更容易保持清洁。 4. I have a feeling that we are being followed. 我有种感觉我们正被人跟踪。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('box', '[bɑːks]', 'n.盒子；箱子；包厢；专席；<口>电视机 n.一拳；巴掌；耳光 n.黄杨；黄杨木 vt.把…装箱；使局限于狭小空间；挡住 v.拳击；打耳光', '1. He has eaten a whole box of chocolates. 他吃了一整盒巧克力。 2. It\'s quite an effort to lift this heavy box. 抬起这只沉重的箱子要花费相当大的力气。 3. They have reserved a box for us in the theatre. 他们在剧院为我们预订了一个包厢。 4. The jurors filed into court one by one and took their places in the jury box. 陪审员们鱼贯进入法庭，在陪审员席内就坐。 5. I gave him a good box on the ear. 我在他耳朵上狠打了一拳。 6. Buy a Chinese little leaf Box decoration, a good tour souvenir, and happiness and luck are always with you. 黄杨木雕像饰，旅游纪念佳品，购上一个，幸福吉祥。 7. The oranges were boxed and sent off quickly. 橘子被装入箱中，然后很快便运走了。 8. Paul will box his opponent tomorrow evening. 明晚保罗将和他的对手进行拳击比赛。', '名词复数: box 过去式: boxed 过去分词: boxed 现在分词: boxing 第三人称单数: boxes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('backward', '[\'bækwərd]', 'adj.向后的；落后的 adv.向后', '1. He took a backward step and ran away. 他向后退了一步,跑了。 2. This part of the country is still backward. 这个国家的这个地区仍很落后。 3. Although he is clever, he is backward in giving his views. 他虽然很聪明，却不善发表他的意见。 4. He looked backward over his shoulder. 他回头向后看。', '副词: backwardly 名词: backwardness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tap', '[tæp]', 'n.龙头；塞子；窃听 n.轻拍；轻敲；鞋掌 v.轻拍；轻击；补鞋掌；选择 v.开发；利用；索要；装龙头；窃听', '1. The water leaked from the tap drop by drop. 水一滴一滴地从龙头漏出来。 2. She left the tap on and the bath ran over. 她没有关水龙头，澡盆里的水溢出来了。 3. The tap on the cask was dirty. 桶上的塞子很脏。 4. The police had put a tap on his phone line. 警察在他的电话上装上窃听器。 5. He felt a tap on his shoulder. 他觉得有人轻拍他的肩膀. 6. The tooth hurts when I tap it. 我轻敲时牙齿会痛。 7. We should tap natural resources. 我们应该开发自然资源。', '过去式: tapped 过去分词: tapped 现在分词: tapping 第三人称单数: taps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('parallel', '[\'pærəlel]', 'adj.平行的；相同的；类似的；并联的 n.对比；平行线(面)；双杠；相似物 vt.相比；相应；与 ... 平行', '1. In the parallel world, there might be an answer for everything. 在平行世界里,似乎有一切的答案。 2. Parallel processing is the most important peculiarity in this design. 其中,并行化的设计理念是该设计的最大特点。 3. The railway lines run parallel to the road. 铁路线和那条道路平行。 4. My experience in this matter is parallel to yours. 在这件事情上，我的经验和你的类似。 5. It is inappropriate to draw such a parallel. 这种比拟是不恰当的。 6. No one can parallel him in Math. 在数学方面无人能与他匹敌。', '过去式: paralleled/parallelled 过去分词: paralleled/parallelled 现在分词: paralleling/parallelling 第三人称单数: parallels/parallels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glimpse', '[ɡlɪmps]', 'n.一瞥；一闪；略微；隐约感觉 v.瞥见', '1. He caught a glimpse of me when I passed by. 当我走过时，他瞥了我一眼。 2. A glimpse of her face will tell you that she is innocent. 你只要一看见她的脸就会明白，她是无辜的。 3. I only caught a glimpse of him sitting in the car, so I can\'t tell exactly what he looked like. 我只瞥见他坐在车里，所以我无法确切说出他长得什么样。 4. He caught a glimpse of her before she banished into the crowd. 他看见她一闪就在人群中消失了。 5. I glimpsed at her among the crowd before she disappeared from sight. 就在她即将消失在人群里之前，我瞥见了她。', '名词: glimpser 过去式: glimpsed 过去分词: glimpsed 现在分词: glimpsing 第三人称单数: glimpses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('meanwhile', '[\'miːnwaɪl]', 'adv.其间；同时', '1. Father was cutting the grass, and meanwhile mother was planting roses. 父亲在剪草,母亲在种玫瑰。 2. Meanwhile, my debts were mounting up. 同时，我的债务还在不断增加。 3. Meanwhile they set aside part of their funds for the motorized boats. 与此同时,他们拨出一部分资金购买机动帆船。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('zeal', '[ziːl]', 'n.热情；热忱', '1. They plunged into their work with immense zeal. 他们以极大的热情投入工作。 2. He shows great zeal for knowledge. 他表现出极大的求知热情。 3. His zeal will soon burn itself out. 他的热忱很快就会冷淡下来的。 4. Entire employee zeal is expecting your presence! 酒店全体员工热忱期待着您的光临！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('donate', '[\'doʊneɪt]', 'v.捐赠；捐献', '1. I can donate one hundred dollars at best. 我充其量只能捐助100美元。 2. We donate to the school endowment fund every year. 我们每年向学校的捐赠基金捐款。 3. The government calls on the youth to donate their blood voluntarily. 政府号召青年义务献血。', '名词: donator 过去式: donated 过去分词: donated 现在分词: donating 第三人称单数: donates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pill', '[pɪl]', 'n.药丸；药片 v.服用药丸；把 ... 制成药丸；<俚>投票反对', '1. Father must take his pill on the hour. 父亲必须在每点钟准点吃药丸。 2. The baby spat out the nasty pill. 婴儿吐出了难吃的药丸。 3. This pill will help to settle your nerves. 你吃了这片药神经就不那麽紧张了。 4. His mother told him to have a vitamin pill before leaving. 他妈妈让他在走之前吃一颗维生素药丸。 5. She was nervous about returning to the pill because of worries about a possible cancer risk. 因为担心可能患癌症的风险，她对再服用药丸很紧张。', '过去式: pilled 过去分词: pilled 现在分词: pilling 第三人称单数: pills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('formulate', '[\'fɔːrmjuleɪt]', 'v.用公式表示；系统地阐述；规划；制订', '1. Survey the material first to get a sense of it: formulate some questions. 考查原始材料首先要了解它的意义：用公式解答问题。 2. He formulated his thought clearly. 他清楚确切地表达了自己的思想。 3. He struggled to formulate an answer. 他努力字斟句酌地回答。 4. He thought it time to formulate some plan of action. 他认为这是该筹划一些行动计划的时候了。', '名词: formulation 过去式: formulated 过去分词: formulated 现在分词: formulating 第三人称单数: formulates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('millimeter', '[\'mɪləˌmiːtə]', 'n.毫米', '1. We measure rainfall by the millimeter. 我们以毫米测量雨量。 2. These dust particles are millimeter sized splinters from asteroids and orbit in the ecliptic plane of the planets. 这些尘埃颗粒来自小行星，只有毫米般大小，沿着行星的黄道平面轨道飞行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('until', '[ən\'tɪl]', 'prep.直到 ... 的时候；在...以前；直到…为止 conj.直到 ... 时候才 ...；在...之前；直到...的程度；直到…为止', '1. The heat did not relax until midnight. 直到半夜，炎热才缓解。 2. We did not notice this matter until yesterday. 直到昨天我们才注意到这件事。 3. She can\'t leave until Friday. 在星期五之前她不能离开。 4. He put off his departure until his sister came. 他推迟行期,直到他妹妹来了之后才走。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('technology', '[tek\'nɑːlədʒi]', 'n.技术；工艺；工艺学', '1. The government saw the introduction of new technology as vital. 政府认为引进新技术至关重要。 2. Britain is behind Japan in developing modern technologies. 在发展现代技术方面英国落后于日本。 3. He majors in engine technology in this college. 他在这所学院主修发动机工艺。 4. They are studying chemical technology. 他们在研究化学工艺学。', '名词复数: technologies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('membership', '[\'membərʃɪp]', 'n.成员资格；会员全体；从属关系', '1. They rejected his application for membership. 他们拒绝考虑他的成员资格申请。 2. Method can be used in code to verify membership in a role. 方法验证角色中的成员资格。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relief', '[rɪ\'liːf]', 'n.减轻；解除；轻松；浮雕；救济(品)；安慰；替代 adj.提供救济的；文本的', '1. The pills gave her some relief. 药片减轻她一些痛苦。 2. This medicine will give you quick relief. 这种药将迅速解除你的病痛。 3. A doctor\'s life is consecrated to the relief of suffering. 医师的一生奉献于解除世人的疾苦。 4. His jokes provided some comic relief in what was really a dull speech. 他说的笑话给极沉闷的讲话增加几分轻松气氛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exceed', '[ɪk\'siːd]', 'vt.超过；超出 vi.领先', '1. His knowledge of history exceeds mine. 他的历史知识超过我。 2. Demand began to exceed supply. 开始供不应求。 3. The fine shall not exceed $300. 罚款不超过三百美元。', '过去式: exceeded 过去分词: exceeded 现在分词: exceeding 第三人称单数: exceeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('publication', '[ˌpʌblɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.出版；发行；出版物；公布；发表', '1. The publication of his book will be next month. 将在下个月出版他的书。 2. Congress has approved a new publication law. 国会已通过一项新的出版法。 3. Publication of the newspaper will discontinue at the end of June. 该报将於六月底停止发行。 4. They voted that the publication of the journal be continued. 他们投票决定继续发行那本杂志。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('doorway', '[\'dɔːrweɪ]', 'n.门口', '1. They stood in the doorway chatting. 他们站在门口闲聊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('magnitude', '[\'mæɡnɪtuːd]', 'n.大小；重要；光度；（地震）级数；（星星）等级', '1. I want to know the magnitude of this equipment. 我想知道这个设备的大小。 2. The magnitude of the epidemic was frightening. 这种流行病传播范围之广令人惶惶不安。 3. I had not realized the magnitude of the problem. 我没意识到这个问题的重要性。 4. The main quake was estimated at magnitude 6.6. 据估计主震区的震级有6.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conversely', '[\'kɑːnvɜːrsli]', 'adv.相反地', '1. Conversely, defining a new class is less common, but often the crucial step. 相反地，很少定义一个新的类，但这通常是关键的一步。 2. Conversely, when Earth and Mars are near each other, Mars looms large and bright. 相反地，当地球和火星距离较近，火星看上去就显得很大很明亮。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('participate', '[pɑːr\'tɪsɪpeɪt]', 'vi.参加；参与 vt.分享', '1. Everyone in the class is expected to participate in the discussion. 希望全班同学参加讨论。 2. In the ancient Greek Olympics, only men were allowed to participate in it. 在古希腊奥运会中,只允许男人参加比赛。 3. I don\'t want to participate in the English party. 我不想参加英语晚会。 4. Everyone in the class is expected to participate in the discussion. 希望全班同学参加讨论。 5. I participate your suffering and joy. 我和你同甘共苦。', '形容词: participative 名词: participation 过去式: participated 过去分词: participated 现在分词: participating 第三人称单数: participates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('literature', '[\'lɪtrətʃər]', 'n.文学；文献；<口>印刷品', '1. She is fond of polite literature. 她喜爱风雅文学。 2. He destroyed feudal ideas in literature. 他摧毁了文学中的封建思想。 3. The principal literature comes from zoology. 主要文献都来自动物学。 4. Beijing was first named ji in literature. 北京最早见于文献的名称叫做蓟。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ritual', '[\'rɪtʃuəl]', 'n.仪式；典礼；宗教仪式；固定程序 adj.仪式的；老规矩的；惯常的', '1. Don\'t be overly solemn or feel that you are taking part in some special ritual; 不要太严肃,或觉得自己正在进行某种仪式; 2. She objects to the ritual of organized religion. 她反对规范的宗教仪规。 3. A strange ritual was enacted before our eyes. 在我们眼前展现出一种奇特的仪式. 4. He performed his ablution before the ritual. 他在典礼前沐 5. So nightly baths have become a part of their ritual even to this day. 所以晚间沐浴成为他们结束一天仪式的一部分。', '副词: ritually');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anxious', '[\'æŋkʃəs]', 'adj.渴望的；忧虑的', '1. The whole country was anxious for peace. 全国上下都渴望和平。 2. I am anxious to compare my fancy with reality. 我焦切地把我的想象同现实作一番比较。 3. Small businesses are anxious to experiment with computers. 小型企业都急于试用计算机。 4. She was anxious to enlighten me about the events that led up to the dispute. 她急着要使我明白引起这场争执的那些事情。', '副词: anxiously 名词: anxiousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('malignant', '[mə\'lɪɡnənt]', 'adj.有恶意的；恶性的；有害的', '1. This is a kind of very malignant tumor. 这是一种很恶性的肿瘤。 2. Malignant gliomas are more aggressive in older people. 恶性的神经胶质瘤在老人身上更具有攻击性。 3. Indeed, not all viruses are malignant. 事实上，并非所有的病毒都是有害的。 4. At any rate, magical practices seem to have assumed a more malignant form in Nevis than in some of the other islands. 无论如何，在奈利斯岛上，魔法的习俗比在一些其他岛屿上似乎采取了一种更为有害的方式。', '副词: malignantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('underlying', '[ˌʌndər\'laɪɪŋ]', 'adj.潜在的；隐含的；在下面的；基本的；<经>优先的 动词underlie的现在分词', '1. This word has its underlying meaning. 这个单词有它潜在的含义。 2. The underlying assumption is that the amount of money available is limited. 隐含的假定是可用的资金有限。 3. We dug down to the underlying rock. 我们往下挖直到碰到了下面的石块。 4. The underlying idea is an appealing one. 基础的概念是一种吸引人的概念。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elbow', '[\'elboʊ]', 'n.手肘；扶手；急弯 v.用手肘推开；推挤', '1. He barked his elbow on the wall. 他碰到墙上，肘部擦破了皮。 2. You jogged my elbow and spoiled what I was drawing. 你撞到了我的手肘，弄坏了我正在画的图画。 3. He tried to elbow me off the line in the lunchroom. 他想用肘把我挤出餐厅的候餐行列。 4. He elbowed his way through the crowd. 他在人群中挤出一条路。', '过去式: elbowed 过去分词: elbowed 现在分词: elbowing 第三人称单数: elbows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('simplify', '[\'sɪmplɪfaɪ]', 'vt.简化；使简单', '1. That will simplify my task. 那可简化了我的工作。 2. She simplified the instructions so that the children could understand them. 她简化了指令以便于儿童理解。 3. The whole process has now been greatly simplified. 整个程序被极大地简化了。 4. Can you simplify your language a little? 你能不能把你的语言改得简单一点?', '名词: simplification 过去式: simplified 过去分词: simplified 现在分词: simplifying 第三人称单数: simplifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('physicist', '[\'fɪzɪsɪst]', 'n. 物理学家； <古>自然科学家', '1. The physicist fudged on his experimental data. 那位物理学家捏造实验数据。 2. He came to the fore as a physicist at an early age. 他在早年就成了杰出的物理学家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('excite', '[ɪk\'saɪt]', 'vt.使兴奋；使激动；刺激；激起', '1. The good news excited everybody. 这个好消息使每一个人都很兴奋。 2. Nothing seemed to surprise or excite him. 好像他对什么事情都不惊讶或兴奋似的。 3. Don\'t excite him. He remembers nothing but his daughter. 不能让他太激动,他现在只记得跟他女儿有关的事。 4. Strong coffee excites your nerves. 浓咖啡刺激神经。', '过去式: excited 过去分词: excited 现在分词: exciting 第三人称单数: excites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prescribe', '[prɪ\'skraɪb]', 'v.开处方；规定，命令，指示；限制，限定', '1. I\'ll prescribe for you as soon as I get the report. 我拿到报告就给你开处方。 2. What medicine did the doctor prescribe for your illness? 医生开了什么药来治你的病？ 3. The law prescribes heavy penalties for this offence. 法律规定对这种不法行为从严惩处。 4. Regulations prescribe that a lawyer draw up the paper. 条文规定必须由律师拟定此公文。', '名词: prescriber 过去式: prescribed 过去分词: prescribed 现在分词: prescribing 第三人称单数: prescribes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extent', '[ɪk\'stent]', 'n. 广度； 宽度； 长度； 大小； 范围； 程度 n. [律]<英>扣押； <美>临时所有权令', '1. A particle has no extent so that its position is a point. 质点没有广度因此它的位置是一个点。 2. As a result, the Census Bureau should obtain a better picture of the extent of intermarriage in the United States. 这样，人口普查局就能够更好地了解美国异族通婚的广度。 3. Percentage increase in extent size. 范围大小增加的百分比。 4. The extent of the regions was determined by the descriptor basicity. 这三个数据区的范围大小是由算符的碱性度决定的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('decrease', '[dɪ\'kriːs]', 'v.减少；减小；降低 n.减少；降低', '1. They are making further efforts to decrease military spending. 他们正在做进一步的努力来减少军费开支。 2. His interest in this subject gradually decreases. 他对这门学科的兴趣逐渐减退。 3. The government projected a tax decrease. 政府计划降低税收。 4. They tried to decrease the costs. 他们设法降低成本。 5. The new treatment led to a huge decrease in the number of deaths. 新的疗法使死亡率急剧减少。', '副词: decreasingly 过去式: decreased 过去分词: decreased 现在分词: decreasing 第三人称单数: decreases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hug', '[hʌɡ]', 'v.拥抱；紧抱；抱有；挨着 n.拥抱；紧抱', '1. It\'s common to hug when people meet in the US. 在美国,见面拥抱是件很平常的事。 2. He hurries down the gangplank to hug his waiting wife. 他匆匆忙忙走下跳板,张开双臂去拥抱等候着他的妻子。 3. The child was hugging her doll. 那孩子紧抱着她的洋娃娃。 4. He\'ll never change, and will hug his cherished beliefs. 他不会改变的，他将永守他所抱的信仰。 5. He greeted her with a loving hug. 他以一个深情的拥抱来迎接她。', '形容词: huggable 名词: hugger 过去式: hugged 过去分词: hugged 现在分词: hugging 第三人称单数: hugs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rigid', '[\'rɪdʒɪd]', 'adj.坚硬的；严格的；固执的；僵硬的；刻板的', '1. The tent has a rigid support. 帐篷有一个坚硬的支柱。 2. He is a man of very rigid principles. 他是一个原则性很强的人。 3. He\'s very rigid in his ideas. 他的想法非常固执。 4. She was rigid with fear. 她害怕得全身僵住了。', '副词: rigidly 名词: rigidness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('narrow', '[\'næroʊ]', 'adj.有限的；狭窄的；精密的；度量小的 n.海峡；隘路；狭窄部份 v.变窄', '1. The shop sells only a narrow range of goods. 这家商店商品的种类有限。 2. The heavy traffic crawled through the narrow tunnel. 拥挤的车辆慢吞吞地穿过狭窄的隧道。 3. The gate is too narrow for a car. 大门太窄，汽车进不去。 4. What does the word mean in its narrowest sense? 这个词的最狭义的意思是什麽? 5. This is a narrow sea that parts the French and English. 这是个分开法国和英国的海峡。 6. They planed to narrow the gap between imports and exports. 他们计划缩小进出口的差额。', '形容词: narrowish 副词: narrowly 比较级: narrower 最高级: narrowest 名词: narrowness 过去式: narrowed 过去分词: narrowed 现在分词: narrowing 第三人称单数: narrows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('who', '[huː]', 'pron.谁 abbr.世界卫生组织(=World Health Organization)', '1. People who cannot speak can talk by using signs. 不会说话的人可以用手势沟通。 2. Who do you think you are? 你以为你是谁？ 3. She looked wretched and forlorn, despairing of the arrival of a friend who had promised to meet her. 她看上去又可怜又孤独，对于答应来看她的朋友的到来已不抱希望。 4. He is a leader who is magnanimous in victory. 他是个在胜利时宽宏大度的领袖。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fast', '[fæst]', 'adj.快的；迅速的；紧的；牢固的；放荡的 adv.快速地；紧紧地；放荡地；深深地 n.斋戒；禁食；系泊用具 v.斋戒；禁食', '1. I like fast music. 我喜欢节奏快的音乐。 2. The star was whipped into a fast car and driven off. 那个明星迅速上了一辆汽车疾驶而去。 3. The post is fast in the ground. 那柱子牢牢地埋在地里. 4. He led a fast life. 他过着放荡的生活。 5. He ran fast enough to catch the thief. 他跑得飞快，足以抓住那小偷。 6. The priest had only water and bread during his three week fast. 牧师在三个星期的斋戒期间只进食水和面包。 7. They have to fast from dawn to dusk. 他们一整天都得禁食。', '比较级: faster 最高级: fastest 过去式: fasted 过去分词: fasted 现在分词: fasting 第三人称单数: fasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('out', '[aʊt]', 'adv.出；在外；完 prep.向外；在外面 v.出来；暴露；驱逐；熄灭；伸出；公开…的同性恋身份', '1. His book came out last month. 他的书上个月出版了。 2. He took out a book from the case. 他从箱子里拿出一本书。 3. Students may not stay out after midnight. 学生午夜后不得在外逗留。 4. I went out into the cold and got a chill. 我走到户外的冷空气里打了个寒颤。 5. They heard a yap and ran out of the house. 他们听见了一声狂吠就跑出了屋外。 6. The truth will out. 真相终将大白于天下。', '过去式: outed 过去分词: outed 现在分词: outing 第三人称单数: outs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hypothesis', '[haɪ\'pɑːθəsɪs]', 'n.假说；假设；前提；猜测', '1. The hypothesis promptly attracted some interest. 这个假说很快引起了注意。 2. The validity of the hypothesis can be tested. 这种假说的可靠性是经得起考验的。 3. His hypothesis turned out to be correct. 事实证明他的假设是正确的。 4. The survey result consisted with our hypothesis. 调查结果和我们的假设相一致。', '名词复数: hypotheses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pile', '[paɪl]', 'n.堆；大量；绒面；桩；<俚>大笔钱财 高大的旧建筑 v.堆积；积累；拥入；夸张', '1. We put the books in piles on the floor. 我们把书在地板上堆起来。 2. I have a huge pile of letters to deal with. 我有一大堆信件要处理。 3. The thick pile of a luxurious bath towel touches soft. 这块华丽浴巾的厚绒面摸起来很柔软。 4. He has made a study on depth effect of pile foundation. 他对桩基深度效应进行了探讨。 5. The little boy is piling up his building blocks. 小男孩正在搭积木。', '形容词: piled 过去式: piled 过去分词: piled 现在分词: piling 第三人称单数: piles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('satellite', '[\'sætəlaɪt]', 'n.卫星；人造卫星', '1. Troop movements can be observed from space by a satellite. 藉助卫星可观察到部队的调动。 2. The equipment picked up the signal from the satellite. 这设备收到了卫星发出的信号。 3. The bbc is hooked up with Australian television by satellite. 英国广播公司通过卫星与澳大利亚电视实行联播。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('biography', '[baɪ\'ɑːɡrəfi]', 'n.传记', '1. He likes to read biographies of great men to promote himself. 他喜欢读伟人传记来提高自己。 2. His biography is a saga of scientific research. 他的传记就是一部科研记实。 3. I have read a biography of Abraham Lincoln. 我读过一部亚伯拉罕•林肯的传记。', '名词复数: biographies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compensation', '[ˌkɑːmpen\'seɪʃn]', 'n.补偿；赔偿；赔偿金', '1. My job is hard,but it has its compensations.It is a great delight to pursue what I am interested in. 我拍的工作虽苦,但也有所补偿。能够从事我感兴趣的工作让我很开心。 2. Compensation of injured workers has cost the company a lot. 公司花了一大笔钱赔偿受伤的工人。 3. My job is hard, but it has its compensations—it is my happiness to pursue what I am interested in. 我的工作虽苦,但却有所补偿（有好的方面因而不觉得太苦）。', '形容词: compensational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('model', '[\'mɑːdl]', 'n.模范；模特儿；模型 adj.模范的；作模型用的 v.做模型；模仿；塑造', '1. His mother is a model of industry. 他母亲是勤劳的模范。 2. Lily is a fashion model. 莉莉是个时装模特儿。 3. The model has an individual way of dressing. 这个模特儿有著独特的穿衣方式。 4. He showed us a model of the new office building. 他给我们看了新办公楼的模型。 5. They are a model couple. 他们是一对模范夫妻。 6. She models in clay. 她用粘土做模型。', '名词: modeler 过去式: modeled/modelled 过去分词: modeled/modelled 现在分词: modeling/modelling 第三人称单数: models');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('honor', '[\'ɑːnər]', 'n.荣誉；荣幸；尊敬；信用；正直；贞洁 vt.尊敬；使荣幸；对...表示敬意；兑现', '1. He stained the family honor. 他玷污了家族的荣誉。 2. I consider it a great honor to be invited to dinner. 我认为能被邀请参加晚宴是很大的荣幸。 3. He won honor for his courage. 他以勇气赢得大家的尊敬。 4. I see no need to honor a pact with an evil beast, Mikhail. 我认为没有必要跟一个邪恶怪兽讲信用，米克黑尔。 5. November 11th is Veterans Day, when Americans honor those who served in the military. 11月11日是美国老兵纪年日，是美国人表达其对军人尊敬的日子。', '名词: honorer 过去式: honored 过去分词: honored 现在分词: honoring 第三人称单数: honors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('routine', '[ruː\'tiːn]', 'n.例行公事；常规；无聊 adj.常规的；例行的；乏味的', '1. We must introduce some system into our office routine. 我们须在我们日常公务中建立一些制度。 2. They did it as a matter of routine. 他们那样做只是例行公事。 3. This type of work rapidly becomes routine. 这种工作很快就变得乏味无聊。 4. You just need to break out of that boring routine. 你只需改变一成不变的无聊生活。 5. The film is a love story, with routine portraits of a conductor and a violinist. 那部电影是一个爱情故事,对於乐队指挥和小提琴手之间的爱情描写都是老一套。', '副词: routinely 名词: routinism');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shut', '[ʃʌt]', 'v.关闭；合拢；停止 adj.关闭的；停止营业的 n.关闭', '1. Please shut the door behind you. 请关上你身后的门。 2. The office will shut down for christmas. 圣诞节办公室将关闭。 3. He decided to shut down the shop. 他决定关闭这家商店。 4. He shut himself away for a month to catch up on his academic work. 他与世隔绝一个月，力图把功课赶上去。 5. She heard the bedroom window blow shut. 她听见卧室的窗户被风刮关了。 6. The jaws snap shut to take a sample. 铁爪急速关闭以抓取样品。', '过去式: shut 过去分词: shut 现在分词: shutting 第三人称单数: shuts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pick', '[pɪk]', 'v.拾；捡；挑选；采摘；找茬；偶然学到 n.拾；捡；选择；采摘；精华 n.鹤嘴锄；镐；琴拨', '1. That sentimental girl likes to pick up the fallen petals on the ground in autumn. 那个多愁善感的女孩喜欢在秋天里拾起地上的落英。 2. He picked the watch up from the carpet. 他从地毯上把表捡起来。 3. We had to find a flat in a hurry--there was no time to pick and choose. 我们只好匆忙找套房子--没有时间挑选了. 4. You should not pick any of the flowers in the park. 你不应该采摘这个公园里的任何一朵花。 5. He bent to the ground to pick up the pen. 他弯腰从地上拾起钢笔。 6. He breaks up strong ground with a pick. 他用镐刨开坚硬的地面。', '名词: picker 过去式: picked 过去分词: picked 现在分词: picking 第三人称单数: picks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('office', '[\'ɔːfɪs]', 'n.办公室；职务；事务；（政府部门的）部、 局、 厅；有特定用途的房间或建筑物', '1. He keeps his office neat and tidy. 他保持办公室清洁整齐。 2. The corridor opens into his office. 这走廊通到他的办公室。 3. He held this office for ten years. 他担任这一职务有十年。 4. Now he holds the office of Foreign Minister. 他现在担任外交部长职务。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wipe', '[waɪp]', 'v.擦；揩；抹；拭去；消除；用力打 n.擦拭；抹布', '1. She wiped her tears away. 她擦掉了眼泪。 2. I wiped my shoes on the mat before I came in. 我在进门前把鞋在垫子上擦了擦。 3. When you have washed the car , wipe it down well . 你把汽车冲洗过后，要好好用布揩拭一下。 4. He tried to wipe out the memory of his former girlfriend. 他试图抹去对前任女友的回忆。 5. Please give the table mats a quick wipe. 请把桌上的盘碗垫擦一下。', '过去式: wiped 过去分词: wiped 现在分词: wiping 第三人称单数: wipes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pay', '[peɪ]', 'v.支付；赢利；受益；付出代价 n.薪资；雇用；有良好信用的人 adj.要钱的；具有开采价值的', '1. I\'d like to pay with my credit card. 我想用信用卡支付。 2. My firm pays well. 我公司工酬优厚。 3. Let me pay for dinner. 晚饭让我来付。 4. You\'ve got to be able to make your business pay well. 你得设法使你的生意赢利。 5. He doesn\'t like that job, but the pay is good. 他不喜欢那工作,但薪水很高。 6. This is a pay telephone. 这是缴费电话。', '过去式: paid 过去分词: paid 现在分词: paying 第三人称单数: pays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('monetary', '[\'mʌnɪteri]', 'adj.货币的；金融的', '1. The monetary unit of the US is the dollar. 美国的货币单位是元。 2. He has changed his stance on monetary union. 他已经改变了对货币联盟的态度。 3. The monetary system of some countries used to be based on gold. 过去有些国家的货币制度是金本位制的。 4. The current monetary policy is strangling the economy. 现行金融政策抑制了经济的发展。', '副词: monetarily');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cellar', '[\'selər]', 'n.地窖；地下室 vt.把 ... 藏入地窑', '1. This wine cellar stays at an even temperature all year round. 这个酒窖常年保持恒温。 2. The cellar floods whenever it rains heavily. 一下大雨地窖里就灌满了水。 3. The cheese molded in the damp cellar. 乳酪在潮湿的地下室中长了霉。 4. They were ensconced in the cellar. 他们躲在地下室里。 5. The wine has been cellared for ten years. 酒在地窖里存了十年。', '过去式: cellared 过去分词: cellared 现在分词: cellaring 第三人称单数: cellars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('basket', '[\'bæskɪt]', 'n.篮；篓；筐；[篮]球篮；投篮得分', '1. Several baskets of fruit were eaten at the party. 宴会上，大家吃掉了好几篮水果。 2. The little girl stared at the little cats tumbling over each other in their basket. 小女孩凝视着在篮子里互相翻来滚去的小猫。 3. Put the scraps of paper in the wastepaper basket. 把纸屑丢进废纸篓。 4. There are just a few apples in the basket. 筐里只剩下有数几个苹果了。', '名词: basketful');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('translate', '[træns\'leɪt]', 'v.翻译；解释；转移；调动', '1. I need to translate it into English. 我必须把它译成英语。 2. Be you plan to translate the novel? 你计划翻译这部小说吗？ 3. I translate his silence as a protest. 我把他的沉默解释为抗议。 4. It is hard to translate the animal\'s behaviour . 那种动物的行为很难解释。', '形容词: translatable 名词: translatability 过去式: translated 过去分词: translated 现在分词: translating 第三人称单数: translates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('divorce', '[dɪ\'vɔːrs]', 'n.分离；离婚 vt.使分离；与 ... 离婚 vi.离婚', '1. They demanded the divorce of the subsidiary from the parent firm. 他们要求子公司与母公司分离。 2. Boredom is not a ground for divorce. 日久生厌不能成为离婚的理由。 3. She has filed a petition for divorce. 她已向法院申请离婚。 4. Divorce has become an everyday occurrence. 离婚已成为每天都有的事了。 5. He is unable to divorce fantasy from reality. 他不能将幻想与现实分开。 6. My information is they\'re going to divorce. 我所得到的信息是他们打算离婚。', '过去式: divorced 过去分词: divorced 现在分词: divorcing 第三人称单数: divorces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('indispensable', '[ˌɪndɪ\'spensəbl]', 'adj.不可缺少的', '1. The computer is now an indispensable tool in many businesses. 目前计算机是很多公司不可或缺的用具。 2. Air is indispensable to life. 空气是生命所必需的东西。 3. A good dictionary is indispensable for learning a foreign language. 学习外语离不开好的词典。 4. Air, food and water are indispensable to life. 空气，食物，水皆为生命不可缺者。', '副词: indispensably 名词: indispensability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kilo', '[\'kiːloʊ]', 'pref.表示“千” abbr.千克；公斤(=kilogram/kilogramme)', '1. The tomatoes cost two yuan a kilo. 蕃茄二元一公斤。 2. I\'d like one kilo of apples, please. 给我称一公斤苹果。', '名词复数: kilos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('household', '[\'haʊshoʊld]', 'n.家庭；户 adj.家庭的；家喻户晓的', '1. The whole household got up early last Sunday. 上个星期天全家人都起得很早。 2. He peddled small articles around the town from household to household. 他在镇上挨家挨户兜售一些小件物品。 3. I disputed with my wife on household expenses. 我跟太太争论有关家庭费用的问题。 4. Microsoft has become a household word. 微软已经成为一个家喻户晓的名词。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enable', '[ɪ\'neɪbl]', 'vt.使能够；使可能', '1. Listening to music enables us to feel relaxed. 听音乐能使我们放松。 2. A dog\'s ears enable it to hear the least sound. 狗的耳朵使它能听到极细微的声音。 3. This train will enable me to get there in time. 这列火车能使我及时到达那儿。 4. Hobbies may enable you to make many friends. 业余爱好能够使你结识很多朋友.', '名词: enabler 过去式: enabled 过去分词: enabled 现在分词: enabling 第三人称单数: enables');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inland', '[ˌɪn\'lænd]', 'adj.内陆的；国内的 adv.内陆地 n.内陆', '1. Chongqing in his plan is to be an inland Shanghai. 在他的计划里，重庆要成为内陆的上海。 2. Sea winds that blow inland from the west are warmed by a current of warm water that flows through the Pacific Ocean. 从太平洋来的温暖的洋流使得从西吹过内陆的海风变得温暖。 3. We spent a week by the coast before going inland. 在去内陆前，我们在海边住了一个星期。 4. Stockell didn\'t get very far inland that morning. 那天早晨，斯托克并未深入内陆多远。', '名词: inlander');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('refuge', '[\'refjuːdʒ]', 'n.避难；避难所；庇护 v.庇护；避难', '1. They took refuge in a cave yesterday. 他们昨天是在一个洞里避难的。 2. It is a classic sanctuary in which the rationalist fancy may take refuge. 这是一所古雅的圣殿，理性主义者可以躲在其中。 3. A small cave was the only refuge from the cold. 小洞穴是唯一的避寒处。 4. They were forced to seek refuge from the fighting. 他们被迫寻求庇护，以躲避战争。 5. Drug traffickers refuged in these border areas. 毒品贩子在这些边界地区躲避。', '过去式: refuged 过去分词: refuged 现在分词: refuging 第三人称单数: refuges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plateau', '[plæ\'toʊ]', 'n.高原；平稳；稳定状态 vi.到达平稳阶段', '1. The plateau extends for many miles. 高原连绵许多英里。 2. The ranch is in the middle of a large plateau. 该牧场位于一个辽阔高原的中部。 3. After a period of rapid inflation, price have now reach a plateau. 经急剧通货膨胀之后物价现已趋于平稳。 4. Mortgage rates declined, then reached a plateau. 抵押价格下跌，然后达到稳定水平 5. The athletic footwear market has not yet plateaued. 运动鞋市场并没趋于平稳。', '名词复数: plateaus 过去式: plateaued 过去分词: plateaued 现在分词: plateauing 第三人称单数: plateaus');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hostage', '[\'hɑːstɪdʒ]', 'n.人质', '1. The highjackers held two women hostage. 劫机者扣留两名妇女作人质。 2. It is likely that they will kill the hostage. 可能他们将杀掉人质。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pale', '[peɪl]', 'adj.苍白的；灰白的；暗淡的；无力的 vi.变苍白；变黯淡；相形见绌 n.栅栏', '1. She was pale with fear. 她吓得脸色发白。 2. His pale face has shown his bad health. 他面色苍白，说明他身体不好。 3. The pale eyes seemed to glare past her, the eyebrows frowned, the long jaw hardened. 那双灰白的眼睛仿佛看穿了她的身子，眉头皱着，长下巴发僵。 4. This pale child of the Parisian faubourgs livesdevelops, makes connections, \"grows supple\" in suffering, in the presence of social realitiesof human things, a thoughtful witness. 巴黎近郊的脸色灰白的孩子，面对着令人深省的社会现实和人间事物，活着，成长着，在苦难中沉下去，浮上来。 5. She paled with shock at the news. 她听到那消息大惊失色。', '副词: palely 比较级: paler 最高级: palest 名词: paleness 过去式: paled 过去分词: paled 现在分词: paling 第三人称单数: pales');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('island', '[\'aɪlənd]', 'n.岛；岛屿；岛状物', '1. This island is accessible only by boat. 这个小岛只能坐小船去。 2. This island is no longer a dependency of the USA. 这个小岛不再是美国的属地。 3. Cocos are everywhere in Hainan Island. 海南岛上到处都是椰子树。 4. The experts are exploring every part of the island. 专家们正在勘查这个岛的各个部分。', '过去式: islanded 过去分词: islanded 现在分词: islanding 第三人称单数: islands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cast', '[kæst]', 'v.掷；抛；投；铸造；指定演员；加起来；投射(目光)；投(票)；预测 n.演员阵容；投掷；[医]固定用敷料', '1. The angler cast her line into the stream. 那个垂钓者把鱼线掷进了小溪里。 2. The storm cast the little rowboat onto the rocks. 风暴把这条小划艇抛到岩石上。 3. The two world wars cast a shadow over the people all over the world. 两次世界大战在全世界人民中投下了阴影。 4. The metals most frequently cast are iron, steal, aluminum and so on. 最常用来铸造的金属是铁、钢、铝等。 5. The play succeeded thanks to the wonderful performance of all the cast. 由于演员们的精彩表演,这部戏获得了成功。', '过去式: cast 过去分词: cast 现在分词: casting 第三人称单数: casts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abdomen', '[\'æbdəmən]', 'n.腹部', '1. I have a pain in the lower abdomen. 我的下腹部有点痛。 2. The surgeon made a slice in her abdomen. 外科医生在她的腹部开了一条口。 3. He got jabbed in the lower part of his abdomen. 他的下腹部被戳。', '形容词: abdominal 副词: abdominally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('precise', '[prɪ\'saɪs]', 'adj.精确的；恰好的；准确的；严格的', '1. With the new technique, measurement was claimed to be much more precise. 有了这种技术,人们断言测量的结果会精确得多。 2. At the precise moment that I put my foot on the step, the bus started. 恰恰就在我登上公共汽车踏板的时候，车子开动了。 3. I am not clear about the precise bearing of the word in this passage. 我说不准这个字在这段文章里的确切意义是什么。 4. Precise employees are highly appreciated in our company. 我们公司十分欣赏工作态度严谨的员工。', '名词: preciseness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fleet', '[fliːt]', 'n.舰队；船队；机群 adj.快速的；敏捷的；短暂的 vt.使（时间）飞逝 vi.疾飞；掠过；逐渐消失', '1. The fleet is manoeuvring in the Baltic. 该舰队正在波罗的海演习。 2. The general ordered the fleet to remain where they were and wait for the further instructions. 将军命令舰队原地待命。 3. The fleet began to fill away on a northerly course. 船队开始顺风向北航行。 4. That is a fleet horse. 那是一匹快马。 5. On board the ship I fleet time by read detective story. 在船上我读侦探小说，借以消磨时间。 6. A plane fleeted over the top of the hill. 一架飞机掠过山顶。', '副词: fleetly 比较级: fleeter 最高级: fleetest 名词: fleetness 过去式: fleeted 过去分词: fleeted 现在分词: fleeting 第三人称单数: fleets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('escape', '[ɪ\'skeɪp]', 'v.逃跑；逃脱；逃避；被忘掉；泄露；去度假 n.逃跑；逃脱；逃避；泄露；度假；[计算机]退出键', '1. The prisoner has escaped. 犯人逃走了。 2. To my surprise, he could escape from that big fire. 令我惊讶的是,他能够从那场大火里逃脱出来。 3. I had left England to escape from my own future. 我离开英国是为了逃避自己的命运。 4. They came to America to escape political tyranny. 他们为逃避暴政逃到了美洲。 5. The thief jumped into a car and made his escape. 小偷跳上汽车逃走了。', '形容词: escapable 名词: escaper 过去式: escaped 过去分词: escaped 现在分词: escaping 第三人称单数: escapes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('painful', '[\'peɪnfl]', 'adj.痛苦的；疼痛的；费力的', '1. It was painful for him to renounce his son. 宣布与儿子脱离关系对他来说是很痛苦的。 2. His wife\'s death left a painful void in his life. 他妻子的死给他的人生留下了痛苦的空虚感。 3. The sting of a jellyfish is very painful. 让水母刺着是很痛的。 4. The operation was very painful. 手术很痛。', '副词: painfully 名词: painfulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('addict', '[\'ædɪkt]', 'vt.沉溺；使 ... 上瘾 n.耽溺者；上瘾者', '1. The young generation should addict themselves to science. 年轻的一代应该酷爱科学。 2. His tastes addict him to the study of antiquity. 嗜好使他沉迷于研究古代的事物。 3. He was addicted to cocaine. 他吸可卡因上瘾。 4. He is turning into an internet addict. 他快变成网虫了。', '形容词: addictive 过去式: addicted 过去分词: addicted 现在分词: addicting 第三人称单数: addicts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quilt', '[kwɪlt]', 'n.被状物；被子 v.缝被；缝制；用垫料填塞', '1. He bought a heavy quilt for the winter. 他买了一床厚被子过冬。 2. He wake to find that his quilt have slip off the bed. 他醒来发现被子从床上滑下来了。 3. If you air your quilt on such a wet day, it\'ll soak up the moisture. 如果在这么潮湿的天晒被子，被子就会把湿气都吸去。', '名词: quilter 过去式: quilted 过去分词: quilted 现在分词: quilting 第三人称单数: quilts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wolf', '[wʊlf]', 'n.狼；特立独行的人 v.狼吞虎咽', '1. The pups played with the mother wolf. 小狼们跟母狼玩耍。 2. He saw a hungry wolf on the prowl with his telescope. 他通过望远镜看到了一头四处觅食的饿狼。 3. Peter is a good footballer, but he is a lone wolf. 彼得是个好足球队员，但他是个不与人合作的人。 4. I have to wolf down my breakfast, I\'m rushed for time. 我得快点吃完早餐,时间不够了。', '名词复数: wolves 过去式: wolfed 过去分词: wolfed 现在分词: wolfing 第三人称单数: wolfs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('postman', '[\'poʊstmən]', 'n.邮递员 =mailman.', '1. The postman has brought a parcel for you. 邮递员给你送来了一个包裹。 2. Our dog went at the postman again this morning. 今天我们的狗又扑咬邮递员了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('advocate', '[\'ædvəkeɪt]', 'v.提倡；主张 n.拥护者；提倡者；律师；辩护者', '1. Many educators advocate a liberal education. 很多教育家提倡通才教育。 2. We don\'t advocate learning by rote. 死记硬背的学习方法，我们是不提倡的。 3. Many people advocate building more hospitals. 许多人主张增设医院。 4. We advocate higher salaries for teachers. 我们主张涨老师的工资。 5. She is a passionate advocate of education reform. 她是一名教育改革的热情拥护者。', '形容词: advocatory 名词: advocator 过去式: advocated 过去分词: advocated 现在分词: advocating 第三人称单数: advocates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aisle', '[aɪl]', 'n.侧廊；(席位间的)通道', '1. It\'s down on the end of this aisle. 沿着这条走廊走到底就是。 2. I think our seat is near the centre aisle. 我想我们的座位靠近中间走廊。 3. The organ play as the bride come down the aisle. 当新娘沿著通道走过来时，风琴演奏了起来。 4. The girl ushered me along the aisle to my seat. 引座小姐带领我沿著通道到我的座位上去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('regular', '[\'reɡjələr]', 'adj.有规律的；定期的；经常的；正规的；整齐的；规则的', '1. He made a regular visit to his parents. 他定期看望父母亲。 2. We will remain in regular contact with them. 我们将和他们保持经常的联系。 3. Please act according to the regular procedure. 请按照正规的程序行事。 4. He is a handsome young man with regular features. 他是个五官端正的英俊青年。', '副词: regularly 名词: regularity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stab', '[stæb]', 'v.刺；戳；刺伤 n.刺；戳；刺痛；尝试', '1. Good friends stab you in the front. 当面刺痛你的是你的好朋友。 2. He stabbed at the earth with his stick. 他拿手杖戳著地。 3. She stabbed at the air with her finger to emphasize what she was saying. 她手指一戳一戳的，强调她说的话。 4. He stabbed the meat with his fork/stabbed his fork into the meat. 他用叉子叉肉。 5. The hunter made a stab at the wolf, but missed. 猎人向狼刺去，但没有刺中。', '名词: stabber 过去式: stabbed 过去分词: stabbed 现在分词: stabbing 第三人称单数: stabs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cousin', '[\'kʌzn]', 'n.堂(或表)兄弟(姐妹)', '1. I hear from my cousin every two weeks. 我每两星期就会收到我表哥的来信。 2. He is a distant cousin of mine. 他是我的一位远房表亲。', '形容词: cousinly 名词: cousinhood');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resident', '[\'rezɪdənt]', 'n.居民；住客；住院医生 adj.居住的', '1. The residents of the town are proud of its new library. 该镇的居民都为镇上新建的图书馆感到自豪。 2. I have been resident in this hotel for two weeks. 我已经在这家旅馆里住了两个星期了。 3. I would get the neurosurgery resident down here. 我想请神经外科住院医师下楼到这儿来。 4. This dove was resident with us all the year round. 这只鸽子一年到头居住在这里和我们为伴。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adopt', '[ə\'dɑːpt]', 'v.采用；收养；接受', '1. They adopt new techniques in raising sheep. 他们采用新的养羊技术。 2. The schools must adopt new methods of teaching foreign languages. 学校应采用新的外语教学法。 3. She was left an orphan and a poor peasant woman adopted her. 她成了孤儿，一位贫农妇女收养了她。 4. To adopt the fruits of sin was to give countenance to it. 收养罪恶的果实就等于纵容罪恶。', '形容词: adoptable 名词: adopter 过去式: adopted 过去分词: adopted 现在分词: adopting 第三人称单数: adopts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('peninsula', '[pə\'nɪnsələ]', 'n.半岛', '1. His house is located on the tip of the peninsula. 他的房子位于半岛的顶端。 2. Leizhou Peninsula lies opposite Hainan Island. 雷州半岛正对着海南岛。', '形容词: peninsular');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seed', '[siːd]', 'n.种子 vi.播种；(植物)结实 vt.播种', '1. The farmers were scattering seed on the fields. 农夫把种子撒在田里。 2. Part of every crop is saved for seed. 每一种庄稼都留一部分作种子。 3. Most plants propagate by seed. 大多数植物靠种子繁殖。 4. Do you know about the evolution of a seed into a plant? 你知道从种子发展成为植物的过程吗？ 5. Peasants plough up and seed in the spring ! 农民在春天犁地播种。 6. The fields have been seeded with corn. 田里播种了玉米。', '名词复数: seeds 过去式: seeded 过去分词: seeded 现在分词: seeding 第三人称单数: seeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aside', '[ə\'saɪd]', 'n.旁白；顺便说的话 adv.在一边；另外；离开', '1. This is surely an author\'s aside. 这当然是作者的旁白。 2. He spoke in an aside of his family. 他离开本题谈起他的家庭。 3. She has cast her old friends aside. 她把老朋友都撇在一边。 4. Before it could be spoken another thought turned it aside. 还没有来得及讲出口,却让另外一个念头把它岔了开去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shelter', '[\'ʃeltər]', 'n.避难所；庇护；庇护所 v.保护；隐匿；庇护', '1. The refugees\' main requirements are food and shelter. 难民的主要必需品是食物和住所。 2. In the storm I took shelter under the tree. 暴风雨时，我正在树下躲避。 3. The spectators scuttled for shelter when it began to rain. 一下起雨来，观众就纷纷找地方躲避。 4. People were scrambling madly for shelter. 人们疯了似的抢着往隐蔽处跑。 5. These plants must be sheltered from direct sunlight. 这种植物必须遮起来，免受阳光直射。', '形容词: shelterless 名词: shelterer 过去式: sheltered 过去分词: sheltered 现在分词: sheltering 第三人称单数: shelters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abrupt', '[ə\'brʌpt]', 'adj.突然的；唐突的；意外的；陡峭的', '1. The river takes an abrupt bend to the west. 这河突然向西转弯。 2. His speech comes to an abrupt stop. 他的演讲突然停止了。 3. That young man has an abrupt manner. 那个年轻人态度很无礼。 4. His manner of speaking was quite abrupt. 他的说话方式很唐突。', '副词: abruptly 名词: abruptness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prohibit', '[prə\'hɪbɪt]', 'vt.禁止；妨碍', '1. Smoking is prohibited here. 这里禁止吸烟。 2. We should prohibit the sale of pornographic literature. 我们应该禁止出售淫秽文学。 3. Some areas prohibit dogs or require them to be on a leash at all times. 一些区域禁止狗或者要求一直拴住它们。 4. Rainy weather and fog prohibited flying. 雨天和大雾妨碍了飞行。', '过去式: prohibited 过去分词: prohibited 现在分词: prohibiting 第三人称单数: prohibits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shop', '[ʃɑːp]', 'n.商店；车间 v.逛商店；购物；买东西', '1. The local dress shop is having a sale. 附近的时装店正在大拍卖。 2. The dresses in the shop are priced high. 这家商店的衣服定价很高。 3. That shop has a large connection. 那商店有一大批顾客。 4. I saw both of them at work in the shop. 我看见他们两人都在车间干活。 5. Women in general like to shop for new clothes. 大多数妇女喜欢逛街买新衣服。', '过去式: shopped 过去分词: shopped 现在分词: shopping 第三人称单数: shops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gloomy', '[\'ɡluːmi]', 'adj.阴暗的；忧闷的；前景黯淡的', '1. Being alone in that gloomy house gave me the willies. 我一个人在那所阴暗的房子心里就发毛。 2. A few faint gleams of sunshine lit up the gloomy afternoon. 有几束隐约的阳光使阴暗的下午有些明亮。 3. Her smile is a breath of fresh air in this gloomy office. 她的微笑给沉闷的办公室带来生气。 4. There is a gloomy, overcast expression on his face. 他愁眉苦脸。', '副词: gloomily 比较级: gloomier 最高级: gloomiest 名词: gloominess');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('needle', '[\'niːdl]', 'n.针 vt.用针缝；激怒；嘲弄 vi.缝纫', '1. The needle pierced her finger. 针刺进了她的手指。 2. She pricked herself on a needle. 她被针扎了一下。 3. The road looks beautiful covered by golden pine needles. 这条路上铺满了金黄色的松针，看上去美极了。 4. My mother is needling my coat. 我妈妈在给我缝外套。 5. The girl is good at needling. 这个女孩擅长做缝纫活。', '名词: needler 过去式: needled 过去分词: needled 现在分词: needling 第三人称单数: needles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reflect', '[rɪ\'flekt]', 'v.反映；反射；反省；归咎；显示', '1. Her sad looks reflected the thought passing through her mind. 她忧戚的面容反映出她内心的思想。 2. The results reflect the greatest credit upon all concerned. 这些成绩带给所有有关人员最大的荣誉。 3. The sunlight was reflected in the water. 日光由水面反射出来。 4. I often reflect on the beauty and complexity of life. 我们经常思考人生的美丽与复杂。', '过去式: reflected 过去分词: reflected 现在分词: reflecting 第三人称单数: reflects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whisky', '[\'wɪski]', 'n.威士忌酒 =whiskey(美).', '1. Two whiskies, please. 请来两杯威士忌。 2. This whisky is very good. 这种威士忌非常好。 3. The Scots have distilled whisky for centuries. 苏格兰人用蒸馏法制威士忌酒已有数百年历史。 4. After another glass of whisky I began to feel dizzy. 我又喝了一杯威士忌之后,就觉得头晕目眩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('uneasy', '[ʌn\'iːzi]', 'adj.不自在的 心神不安的 不稳定的；不舒服的', '1. I feel uneasy to make you be injured. 我为了使你受伤感到不安。 2. I\'m uneasy in my mind about the future. 我为前途而忧虑。', '副词: uneasily 比较级: uneasier 最高级: uneasiest 名词: unease');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('machine', '[mə\'ʃiːn]', 'n.机器；做事效率高的人；工具；车辆 v.以机器制造', '1. This machine has been specially adapted for underwater use. 这机器是为水下使用而特别改装的。 2. My mother-in-law has a sewing machine. 我婆婆有一台缝纫机。 3. The team is a well-oiled machine right now. 这个团队现在运转十分良好。 4. He criticized those who had turned politics into a money machine. 他指责那些将政治转变为赚钱工具的人。 5. It will take less time to machine the curtains than to sew them by hand. 用机器织窗帘比用手工缝花的时间要少。', '形容词: machinable 过去式: machined 过去分词: machined 现在分词: machining 第三人称单数: machines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('meaning', '[\'miːnɪŋ]', 'n.意义；含义；重要性；价值 adj.意味深长的', '1. These words are empty of meaning. 这些话毫无意义。 2. This battle is of historic meaning. 这一战具有历史意义。 3. I can\'t apprehend your meaning. 我不明白你的意思。 4. You mistook my meaning entirely. 你完全误解了我的意思。 5. Henry and his wife again interchanged a meaning look. 亨利和他的妻子又互相交换了一个意义深长的眼色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pretty', '[\'prɪti]', 'adv.相当地 adj.漂亮的；秀丽的；好看的 vt.使漂亮 n.漂亮的东西；美人', '1. I am pretty sure that he\'ll say yes. 他会同意的,我对此相当有把握。 2. After six months, I could speak Chinese pretty well. 6个月之后,我就能讲相当好的汉语了。 3. Rachel is a very pretty woman, just like her mother. 瑞秋是一位很漂亮的女性,就像她的母亲一样。 4. What a pretty little garden! 多么漂亮的小花园！ 5. All the pretty women wore their smartest dresses. 所有漂亮的女士都穿著最漂亮的连衫裙。', '副词: prettily 比较级: prettier 最高级: prettiest 名词: prettiness 名词复数: pretties 过去式: prettied 过去分词: prettied 现在分词: prettying 第三人称单数: pretties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('explosion', '[ɪk\'sploʊʒn]', 'n.爆炸；爆炸声；激增；爆发', '1. The atomic explosion is always accompanied by huge fireball. 原子弹爆炸总是伴随着巨大的火球。 2. After the explosion it was some time before the town resumed its everyday routines. 爆炸后经过相当一段时间，这个城镇才恢复了正常的生活秩序。 3. The horse took a fright at the sound of the explosion. 马听到爆炸声受了惊。 4. The explosion was heard a mile away. 那爆炸声一英里外也可以听到。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expect', '[ɪk\'spekt]', 'v.预期；期待；盼望', '1. This is what we expect to happen. 这就是我们所预期将会发生的。 2. He is expected to get through to the finals. 我们期待他进入决赛。 3. At last they got the telegram they had been expecting. 最后他们收到了他们盼望的电报。', '形容词: expectable 副词: expectably 名词: expectedness 过去式: expected 过去分词: expected 现在分词: expecting 第三人称单数: expects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('garlic', '[\'ɡɑːrlɪk]', 'n.大蒜', '1. His breath smelt of garlic. 他呼出的气中有蒜味。 2. This dish needs a touch more garlic. 这菜里要再加点儿蒜。 3. Can you taste the garlic in this stew? 你尝得出炖肉里有大蒜味儿吗? 4. She put several cloves of garlic in the dish. 她在菜里放了几瓣大蒜。', '过去式: garlicked 过去分词: garlicked 现在分词: garlicking 第三人称单数: garlicks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('library', '[\'laɪbreri]', 'n.图书馆；藏书；书房', '1. The town has its own public library and public gardens. 那城市有自己的公用图书馆和公园。 2. In the library, the books on history are all kept in one bay. 在图书馆里，历史方面的书都放在同一隔间里。 3. Professor Hunter has a library of about five thousand books. 汉特教授约有五千册藏书。 4. I found him working in his library when I called. 我去拜访他时看到他在书房里工作。', '名词复数: libraries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abolish', '[ə\'bɑːlɪʃ]', 'vt.废除；革除；消灭', '1. Abraham Lincoln abolished slavery in the United States. 亚伯拉罕·林肯在美国废除了奴隶制。 2. There are many bad customs and laws that ought to be abolished. 有许多不良的习俗和法规应予以废除。 3. They petitioned the government to abolish hanging. 他们向政府请愿，要求废除绞刑。 4. The legislature passed a law to abolish the surtax. 立法机关通过了一项废除附加税的法令。', '形容词: abolishable 名词: abolisher 过去式: abolished 过去分词: abolished 现在分词: abolishing 第三人称单数: abolishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outcome', '[\'aʊtkʌm]', 'n.结果；后果', '1. What was the outcome of your meeting? 你们会晤的结果如何? 2. The outcome of the election is a foregone conclusion. 选举结果已在预料之中。 3. The outcome of the game is beyond his fondest hopes. 比赛结果使他大喜过望。 4. Public interest centres on the outcome of next week\'s by-election. 公众的注意力集中在下周的补选结果上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transmission', '[træns\'mɪʃn]', 'n.传输；传播；播送；变速器', '1. He varied the transmission frequency. 他变换了无线电传送的频率。 2. Animals may serve as a vehicle for viral transmission. 动物可能成为病毒传播的媒介。 3. We now interrupt our normal transmissions to bring you a special news flash. 我们现中断正常节目，播送一条特别新闻。 4. The company has a transmission plant in France. 那家公司在法国有一座变速器工厂。', '形容词: transmissive');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prize', '[praɪz]', 'n.奖品；奖金；奖赏 vt.珍视；估价 adj.奖品的；得奖的；一流的', '1. The boys competed with each other for the prize. 那些男孩子为赢得奖品而互相竞争。 2. First prize in the raffle is a holiday for two in Paris. 抽奖销售的头奖是两个人到巴黎度假旅游。 3. The champion team will win the cup and prize. 比赛的冠军将获得奖杯和奖金。 4. They all concurred in giving him the prize. 他们一致同意给他奖赏。 5. I still prize all those early pamphlets . 我仍珍视所有的那些早期小册子。 6. She will use the prize money to help pay for my education. 她要用这笔奖金支付部分学费。', '过去式: prized 过去分词: prized 现在分词: prizing 第三人称单数: prizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('piston', '[\'pɪstən]', 'n.活塞', '1. All the apprentices rushed to help fit the piston. 徒工们都跑过来帮助装活塞。 2. They use a piston engine instead. 他们改用活塞发动机。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('importance', '[ɪm\'pɔːrtns]', 'n.重要；重要性', '1. Character is of sovereign importance. 人品最为重要。 2. What was said was of prime importance. 说过的那件事是很重要的。 3. This matter is of vital importance to us. 这件事对我们来说至关重要。 4. He emphasized the importance of careful driving. 他强调小心驾驶的重要性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('despatch', '[dɪ\'spætʃ]', 'vt.派遣；迅速处理 n.运送；派遣；急件 =dispatch（美）', '1. A messenger was despatched to take the news to the soldiers at the front. 一名通讯员被派去给前线士兵送消息。 2. We soon despatched the chocolate cake. 我们很快就吃完了巧克力蛋糕。 3. They are then transported to the despatch area. 然后他们被送到发货区。 4. A cable inquiry would ensure early despatch,which is of benefit to you. 如来电询购,当可早日运送,这对你方是有利的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('correspondence', '[ˌkɔːrə\'spɑːndəns]', 'n.通信；信件；相符，相似；一致，相当', '1. We have carried on a correspondence for years. 多年来,我们一直互相通信。 2. I\'ve fallen behind with my correspondence. 我积压了许多信没回。 3. I\'ve got through a lot of correspondence today. 今天我处理了一大批信件。 4. As her private secretary he has access to all her correspondence. 他是她的私人秘书，能接触到她所有的信件。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('meadow', '[\'medoʊ]', 'n.草地；牧场', '1. The bright sun lit up the meadow. 灿烂的太阳照亮草地。 2. A lazy stream winds through the meadow. 一条缓慢流动的溪水蜿蜒曲折流经草地。 3. Cattle were grazing on the meadow. 牛在牧场上吃草。', '形容词: meadowy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lame', '[leɪm]', 'adj.无说服力的；跛足的 vt.使 ... 成残废 n.金属薄板', '1. He gave a lame excuse for being late. 他说了个站不住脚的理由解释他迟到的原因。 2. Mary offered only a lame apology. 玛丽只作了一个站不住脚的辩解。 3. He is lame in one leg and walks with the help of a crutch. 他的一条腿跛了，走路借助于拐杖。 4. The work was hard for the lame old man. 这工作对他这个跛脚的老先生来说是很辛苦的。 5. The accident made him lame in the left leg 出事後他的左腿瘸了', '副词: lamely 比较级: lamer 最高级: lamest 名词: lameness 过去式: lamed 过去分词: lamed 现在分词: laming 第三人称单数: lames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('social', '[\'soʊʃl]', 'adj.社会的；社会阶层的；群居的；社交的；好交际的；合群的 n.社交聚会；社会保障', '1. Her research is centred on the social effects of unemployment. 她的研究课题是失业对社会的影响。 2. Many social services are still provided by voluntary societies in our city. 在我们的城市，许多社会服务仍然是有志愿团体提供的。 3. Social divisions in the city are stark. 城市里各社会阶层有明确的分野。 4. Mrs Brown is known as a social climber. 布朗太太是有名的趋炎附势的人。 5. They are living on the social now. 他们现在靠社会保障金维持生活。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('excitement', '[ɪk\'saɪtmənt]', 'n.激动；兴奋', '1. The excitement quickened my pulse. 激动使我的心跳加快。 2. Her eyes kindled with excitement. 她的眼睛里闪耀出激动的神色。 3. The boys were running in excitement. 男孩们兴奋地跑来跑去。 4. Her heart was throbbing with excitement. 她兴奋得心直跳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('analytic', '[ˌænə\'lɪtɪk]', 'adj.分析的；分解的', '1. The analytic method is dialectical. 分析的方法就是辩证的方法。 2. As the founder and major representative of Analytic Marxism, Cohen makes the sharpest criticism of Nozick who is a right-wing libertarian. 摘要作为分析的马克思主义学派的创立者和首要代表，柯亨对右翼自由至上主义者诺齐克的持有正义理论作了最为犀利的批判。', '副词: analytically 异体字: analytical');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wreck', '[rek]', 'v.使…失事；使…遇难；破坏 n.遇难；残骸；破坏；（船）失事下沉', '1. The ship was wrecked on the rock. 船在岩石上撞毁了。 2. The train wrecked at midnight. 这列火车半夜出轨了。 3. His drinking wrecked their marriage. 他的酗酒毁坏了他们的婚姻。 4. Nobody can wreck the friendship between us. 没有人能破坏我们之间的友谊。 5. They save the cargo from the wreck. 他们从遇难船上抢救出货物。', '过去式: wrecked 过去分词: wrecked 现在分词: wrecking 第三人称单数: wrecks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exercise', '[\'eksərsaɪz]', 'n.运动；练习；作业 vt.运用 vi.锻炼', '1. Exercise is good for your heart and lungs. 对您的心脏和肺,运动也是有益的。 2. I suggest you go on a diet and take more exercise. 我建议你节食,多做运动。 3. Next I\'d like you to do the exercises on page 10. 下面我让你做第10页上的练习。 4. She does her piano exercises in the afternoon. 她每天下午练习钢琴。 5. You should learn how to exercise self-control. 你要学会运用自制力。 6. You should exercise more so as to keep energetic. 你应当多锻炼以保持精力充沛。', '形容词: exercisable 过去式: exercised 过去分词: exercised 现在分词: exercising 第三人称单数: exercises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('volt', '[voʊlt]', 'n.伏特(电压单位)', '1. The unit we use to measure voltage is the volt. 计量电压的单位是伏特。 2. I want to buy a 220 volt transformer. 我要买个二百伏特的变压器。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('antenna', '[æn\'tenə]', 'n.触角；天线', '1. Its ears were small, cup-shaped antennae. 它的耳朵很小,是杯子形状的触角。 2. Its antenna has reached every aspect of social life. 它的触角已经伸向社会生活的每个方面。 3. Extended the radio antenna. 把收音机的天线拉到最长 4. You should fix the television antenna before receiving programs. 接收节目前，你应该先装天线。', '形容词: antennal 名词复数: antennae');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accuse', '[ə\'kjuːz]', 'v.谴责；控告；指责', '1. How dare you accuse me of lying! 你怎敢谴责我说谎! 2. We resolve not to accuse them to avoid troubles. 我们决定不起诉他们 3. I mustered up enough courage to accuse him. 我鼓起足够的勇气控告他。 4. He was accused of incompetence. 他被指责为不称职。', '副词: accusingly 名词: accuser 过去式: accused 过去分词: accused 现在分词: accusing 第三人称单数: accuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wide', '[waɪd]', 'adj.广泛的；广阔的；睁得大的；渊博的；偏离目标的 adv.张的很大地；广阔地；没有完全获胜把握', '1. He is a man of wide interests. 他兴趣广泛。 2. The paper has a wide readership. 该报拥有广泛的读者。 3. Computers have been brought into wide use. 计算机已得到广泛使用。 4. The Asiatic plains are very wide. 亚洲的平原非常广阔。 5. Open your mouth wide when you pronounce this sound. 发这个音时,嘴要张大。', '副词: widely 比较级: wider 最高级: widest 名词: wideness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('smart', '[smɑːrt]', 'adj.时髦的；漂亮的；聪明的；敏捷的；整洁的；厉害的 vi.刺痛；难过；烦恼 n.刺痛；苦恼 adv.（=smartly）', '1. I\'m a smart girl that speaks with a smart accent. 我是个机灵的姑娘，说话带有时髦的腔调。 2. A few months ago they opened a new shop catering exclusively to the smart set. 几个月前他们新开了一家商店，专门向最时髦的人士出售物品。 3. He really cuts a dash in his smart new uniform. 他穿著漂亮的新制服真是神气十足。 4. A smart tie and a dirty collar don\'t go well together. 漂亮的领带与肮脏的领口在一起不相称。 5. His eyes smart at the smoke. 他的眼睛被烟熏痛了。 6. The smart of his wound kept him awake. 伤痛使他无法入睡。', '副词: smartly 比较级: smarter 最高级: smartest 名词: smartness 过去式: smarted 过去分词: smarted 现在分词: smarting 第三人称单数: smarts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expansion', '[ɪk\'spænʃn]', 'n.膨胀；扩展；扩充', '1. Metals undergo expansion when heated. 金属加热时会膨胀。 2. The thermostat is based on the fact that different metals have different coefficients of expansion. 恒温器是以不同的金属有不同的膨胀系数这一事实为根据的。 3. His economic policies paved the way for industrial expansion. 他的经济政策为工业的扩展铺平了道路。 4. The time has come for the firm to consolidate after several years of rapid expansion. 公司经过几年的迅速发展之後，该整顿一下了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('emergency', '[i\'mɜːrdʒənsi]', 'n.突发事件；紧急状态 adj.应急的；紧急的；备用的', '1. She has the ability to keep calm in an emergency. 她有处变不惊的本事。 2. We took the emergency in our stride. 我们泰然地处理了紧急情况。 3. Ring the bell in an emergency. 情况紧急时请按铃。 4. The rioting grew worse and the government declared a state of emergency. 骚乱恶化，政府只得宣布进入紧急状态。 5. He has made every arrangement to meet any emergency. 他已作好了应急的一切准备。', '名词复数: emergencies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scene', '[siːn]', 'n.情景；场；景', '1. The terrible scene was engraved on his memory. 那可怕的情景铭记在他的记忆里。 2. The first scene of the play is the king\'s palace. 剧中的第一个场景是王宫。 3. A new chapter in a novel is something like a new scene in a play. 一部小说中新的一章,就象一出戏中新的一场。 4. He drew a picture of wintry scene. 他画了一幅冬天景色的画。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extinct', '[ɪk\'stɪŋkt]', 'adj.灭绝的；熄灭的；消亡的', '1. This is an extinct species of fish. 这是一种已经灭绝的鱼。 2. This species will be extinct in a few decades. 几十年后这个物种将会灭绝。 3. An extinct volcano can no longer erupt. 一个灭绝的火山已不能再爆发。 4. My hope of getting some employment was extinct. 我要找到工作的希望落空了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('for', '[fər]', 'prep.为；因为；代表；往；支持；关于；给 conj.因为', '1. A party was held for them. 设宴招待他们。 2. They jumped for joy. 他们高兴地跳了起来。 3. I am speaking for all the workers in this firm. 我代表公司全体工作人员讲话。 4. We set off for London. 我们动身去伦敦。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dome', '[doʊm]', 'n.圆屋顶；苍穹；<俚>脑袋；圆形的火山口 vt.加圆屋顶于...上；使成圆屋顶 vi.成圆顶状', '1. Italian architect celebrated for his work during the Florentine Renaissance. His greatest achievement is the octagonal ribbed dome of the Florence cathedral. 布鲁内莱斯基，菲利波1377－1446意大利建筑师，其作品在佛罗伦萨文艺复兴时期享有盛名。其杰作是佛罗伦萨大教堂的八边形肋骨穹隆 2. A transparent dome on the top of an aircraft, through which celestial observations are made for navigation. 天文观测舱，领航舱飞机顶部的一个透明圆顶形结构，航行时可通过它作天文观测 3. Upward pressure from underlying magma domes the surface. 地下岩浆的向上推力使地面成圆顶形。 4. The dome of St. Paul Cathedral is well known in the world. 圣保罗教堂的圆顶闻名于世。', '过去式: domed 过去分词: domed 现在分词: doming 第三人称单数: domes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trim', '[trɪm]', 'v.修剪；削减；装饰；调整帆以适应风向 adj.整洁的；匀称的 n.修剪；整齐；装饰', '1. I\'ll have my hair trimmed tomorrow. 明天我要修剪头发。 2. We have to trim our cost if we want to increase our profit. 我们如果想增加利润，就必须削减开支。 3. They trim their Christmas trees with strings of colored lights. 他们用一串串的彩灯装饰圣诞树。 4. The crew is in trim for the boat-race. 船员们都准备就绪，等待比赛的开始。 5. The new house has a trim appearance. 那幢房子有整洁的外观。 6. I\'d just like a trim and don\'t make it too short. 只需要修剪一下，不要修得太短。', '副词: trimly 比较级: trimmer 最高级: trimmest 名词: trimness 过去式: trimmed 过去分词: trimmed 现在分词: trimming 第三人称单数: trims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('delete', '[dɪ\'liːt]', 'vt.删除', '1. Delete his name from the list. 把他的名字从名单上删去。 2. The attack is to wipe out data, to delete flies, or to format the hard disk. 常见的攻击方式是消除数据、删除文件或者格式化硬盘。 3. Please delete my name from your list. 请把我的名字从你的名单上删除。 4. You cannot delete your standard resource. 您不能删除您的标准资源。', '过去式: deleted 过去分词: deleted 现在分词: deleting 第三人称单数: deletes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spark', '[spɑːrk]', 'vi.闪烁；冒火花；热情回应 vt.激发；引起；向...求爱 n.火星；朝气；情人；俗丽的年轻人', '1. A tiny star can spark in the darkness. 小星星也会在黑暗中发光。 2. Druce lit the cigar, which began to spark and crackle. 德鲁斯点着一支雪茄，这支雪茄发出火花，噼噼啪啪地响起来。 3. He sparked to her plan. 他欣然同意了她的计划。 4. You can spark the spirit of enterprise. 你们可以激发事业上的进取心。 5. A cigarette spark started the fire. 香烟的火星引起这场火灾。', '名词: sparker 过去式: sparked 过去分词: sparked 现在分词: sparking 第三人称单数: sparks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('daytime', '[\'deɪtaɪm]', 'n.白天；日间', '1. I cannot sleep in the daytime. 白日我睡不着。 2. We can\'t see stars in the daytime. 我们不能在白天看到星星。 3. Some animals are inactive during the daytime. 有些动物白天不活动。 4. The temperature was much higher in the daytime than at night. 日间气温比夜间高多了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assignment', '[ə\'saɪnmənt]', 'n.分配；任务；功课；委派；被指定的(课外)作业;(分派的)任务', '1. This is Robert Mundell\'s assignment rule. 这就是罗伯特·蒙代尔的分配原则。 2. He is the best man who can finish the assignment. 他是能完成这项任务的最佳人选。 3. How are you going to get through the assignment? 你将如何完成作业呢? 4. I await assignment at any moment. 我随时听候差遣。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intact', '[ɪn\'tækt]', 'adj.完好无缺的；原封不动的；未经触碰的', '1. Despite his misfortunes, his faith and optimism remained intact. 虽然他遭到一连串的不幸，他的信心和乐观丝毫未减。 2. You may have your money back on this woolen sweater if it is kept clean and intact. 如果羊毛衫保持清洁、完好无缺，您可以退款。 3. The money was returned intact by its finder. 钱原封未动地被捡拾者送还。 4. This stretch of wetlands has remained intact. 这块湿地一直保持着自然的面貌。', '副词: intactly 名词: intactness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deep', '[diːp]', 'adj.深的；深刻的；深奥的；深切的 adv.深深地 n.深处', '1. There is a deep divide between the two factions. 这两派之间有很深的分歧。 2. The deer escaped to the deep forest. 那鹿逃入了丛林深处。 3. His personality left a deep impression on us. 他的人品给我们留下了深刻的印象。 4. It\'s a deep and meaningful conversation. 这是一次深奥而又意义深远的谈话。 5. The ship sank deep into the sea. 船深深地沉入了海底。 6. They got lost in the deep of the forest. 他们在森林深处迷了路。', '副词: deeply 比较级: deeper 最高级: deepest 名词: deepness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('incident', '[\'ɪnsɪdənt]', 'n.事变；事件；插曲 adj.难免的；附带的', '1. The serious incident along the border increased our fears of the war. 边境上的紧张局势加重了我们对战争的忧虑。 2. She couldn\'t erase the incident from her memory. 她难以忘记那次事件。 3. The police are connecting this incident with last week\'s terrorist bombing. 警方认为这次事件和上周的恐怖分子爆炸事件有关。 4. The incident put a dampener on his birthday party. 这件事使得他的生日晚会很扫兴。 5. These diseases are incident to childhood. 儿童易患这类疾病。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('magnetic', '[mæɡ\'netɪk]', 'adj.有磁性的；有吸引力的；催眠术的 n.磁体，磁性物质', '1. The loop becomes magnetic when the current is switched on. 通电时线圈就会有磁性。 2. She has a magnetic personality. 她具有极具吸引力的性格。 3. She was the most magnetic speaker I have ever listened to. 她是我所听过的演讲者中最有吸引力的一位。', '副词: magnetically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surplus', '[\'sɜːrpləs]', 'n.过剩；顺差；盈余 adj.过剩的；多余的', '1. Mexico has a large surplus of oil. 墨西哥有大量过剩的石油。 2. Countries with surplus are called creditor nations. 有顺差的国家则称为债权国。 3. Surpluses of food can be sold for cash. 多余的食物可卖钱。 4. Every country has a lot of surplus labor. 每个国家都有大量的剩余劳动力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outward', '[\'aʊtwərd]', 'adj.向外的；表面的；外部的 adv.向外；在外；表面', '1. A detonation projects an instantaneous pulse of pressure outward in all directions. 爆炸的瞬间会朝各个方向发出向外的压力波。 2. Frost consists of tiny crystals of ice which grow outward from a solid surface. 霜是由冰的微晶组成，它生长在固体表面的外部。 3. The Sun\'s outermost layer begins about 10,000 miles above the visible surface and goes outward for millions of miles. 太阳的最外层从其可见表面的约一万英里处开始，向外延伸数百万英里。 4. And there have been morbid miseries fostered by gloomy creeds, which have led men into profound inner discords that made all outward prosperity of no avail. 悲观的信念孳生了病态的痛苦，致使人类的内部极不和谐，从而使外部的繁荣毫无成果。 5. The walls of the dilapidated shed lean outward. 那座破棚屋的墙向外倾。', '名词: outwardness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guideline', '[\'ɡaɪdlaɪn]', 'n.指导方针；准则', '1. This guideline stresses the deterrence of war. 这一方针注重遏制战争的爆发。 2. The only guideline is to reach the best possible result. 唯一的指导方针,就是获得最好的可能的结果。 3. They see the law only as a general guideline. 他们视法律为一般的准则 4. This guideline is established by general consent. 这个纲领是经多数人同意而制定的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elaborate', '[ɪ\'læbəreɪt]', 'adj.详尽的；复杂的；精心的；精美的 v.详细地说明；用心制作；推敲；变得复杂', '1. He launched into an elaborate explanation of his theory. 他开始详尽地阐发他的理论。 2. Her elaborate hairstyle, to her disappointment, just amused us. 令她失望的是,她复杂的发型只让我们感到好笑。 3. It was not the old man to indulge in elaborate preliminaries. 这位老人向来不做那种煞费苦心的开场白。 4. She had prepared herself for a very elaborate show. 她准备了一场非常精美的表演。 5. She went on to elaborate her argument. 她进而详尽阐述了她的论点。', '副词: elaborately 名词: elaborateness 过去式: elaborated 过去分词: elaborated 现在分词: elaborating 第三人称单数: elaborates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('difference', '[\'dɪfrəns]', 'n.差异；不同；差额；分歧 vt.<罕见用法> 区别', '1. How do you account for the difference between them? 你怎样来解释它们之间的差异呢？ 2. Flowers make no difference to this room. 这房间有没有花没什么区别。 3. It won\'t make much difference whether you go today or tomorrow. 你今天或明天去没有多大关系。 4. This convention makes no difference to the results. 这种习惯做法不会得出不同结果。', '过去式: differenced 过去分词: differenced 现在分词: differencing 第三人称单数: differences');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drug', '[drʌɡ]', 'n.毒品；药 vt.使服麻醉药；使服毒品；掺麻醉药（或毒药）于', '1. They were arrested for drug offences. 他们因贩卖毒品罪而被逮捕。 2. The man formed a habit of taking harmful drugs. 这人养成了服用有害麻醉品的习惯。 3. We are testing the efficacy of a new drug. 我们正在测试新药的功效。 4. His medicine is a drug that can be injected or taken by mouth. 他的药可以注射或口服。 5. They drug the watchman and rob the bank. 他们用药麻醉看守人，然后抢劫银行。', '过去式: drugged 过去分词: drugged 现在分词: drugging 第三人称单数: drugs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('truth', '[truːθ]', 'n.事实；真理；真实；真相', '1. It is far from the truth. 这哪里是事实。 2. The truth verified the allegations. 事实证明了这些说法。 3. Practice is the sole criterion of truth. 实践是检验真理的唯一标准。 4. In science, mistakes always precede the truth. 在科学的领域中，错误一定会出现在真理之前。', '名词复数: truths 形容词: truthful 副词: truthfully');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('leave', '[liːv]', 'v.委托；离开；留给；遗留；遗赠；听任 n.许可；准假；告别 vi.生出叶子', '1. I will leave you to attend to the matter . 我委托你办此事。 2. You can leave it with us for safe keeping for no more than a month, or abandon it. 您可以委托我们替您保管，但为期只有一个月时间，或者您选择放弃。 3. I leave the gay saloon of New York for the green glade of the country. 我离开了纽约欢乐的酒店，来到乡村绿色的林间空地。 4. Please, don\'t forget to hand back your room key before you leave the hotel. 在离开旅馆之前，请不要忘记交还房间的钥匙。 5. It is necessary to seek the Court\'s leave to file a document out of time. 时限过后,必须得到法庭的许可才可以将文件存盘。', '名词: leaver 过去式: left 过去分词: left 现在分词: leaving 第三人称单数: leaves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('man', '[mæn]', 'n.男人；人；男子汉；情人；强者；下属 v.使...振奋；为...配备人手', '1. She married a man who put her on a pedestal. 她嫁给了一个对她十分崇拜的男人。 2. All men are born equal. 人生而平等。 3. He played the man in the time of great trouble. 他在极为困难的时候显示出男子汉的气概。 4. Have you met Jessica\'s new man? 你见过杰西卡的新男朋友吗？ 5. The soldier manned himself for the battle ahead. 那个士兵使自己振作起来以应付眼前的战斗。', '名词复数: men 过去式: manned 过去分词: manned 现在分词: manning 第三人称单数: mans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consider', '[kən\'sɪdər]', 'v.考虑；思考；认为；体谅；注视', '1. Please take time to consider the problem. 请仔细考虑一下这个问题。 2. They did not consider whether they could afford the time or not. 他们没有考虑是否抽得出时间。 3. When you read, don\'t just consider what the author thinks, consider what you think. 当你在阅读的时候,不要只是思考作者在想什么,而是要思考你在想什么。 4. We consider that the driver is not to blame. 我们认为这不是司机的过错。', '名词: consideration 过去式: considered 过去分词: considered 现在分词: considering 第三人称单数: considers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hatred', '[\'heɪtrɪd]', 'n.仇恨；憎恨；敌意；怨恨', '1. His words stirred up my hatred. 他的话激起了我的仇恨。 2. There is implacable hatred between the two nations. 两国之间有无法消除的仇恨。 3. This hatred was generated by racial prejudice. 这种仇恨是由种族偏见引起的。 4. I have a vehement hatred of people who is cruel to animal. 我对残害动物的人怀有强烈的憎恨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bowl', '[boʊl]', 'n.碗；碗状物；圆形露天剧场；季后赛 n.木球；保龄球 v.投球；打保龄球', '1. I have a bowl of cereal every morning. 我每天早晨吃一碗麦片粥。 2. His grandfather gave her an earthenware bowl. 他的祖父给了她一个陶碗。 3. Hollywood Bowl, the huge outdoor amphitheater, is very attractive. 好莱坞圆形的露天剧场非常壮观。 4. If we win, we\'ll have a bowl game this season. 如果我们赢的话,我们就可以去打季后赛。 5. Capitol Hill lawmakers are pressing college football officials to switch the Bowl Championship Series to a playoff system. 国会山立法者给大学足球官员施加压力，让其将保龄球冠军系列赛转变为最后决赛制度。 6. Botham came on to bowl after lunch. 午饭后博瑟姆开始投球。', '过去式: bowled 过去分词: bowled 现在分词: bowling 第三人称单数: bowls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hostile', '[\'hɑːstl]', 'adj.敌对的；怀敌意的', '1. Let\'s hope they will refrain from hostile actions. 希望他们不采取敌对行动。 2. I don\'t like her manner -- she\'s very hostile. 我不喜欢她的态度--待人如仇敌。 3. I don\'t know why she is hostile to me. 我不知道她为什么对我抱有敌意。 4. The new government was hostile to them. 新政府对他们怀有敌意。', '副词: hostilely');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outside', '[ˌaʊt\'saɪd]', 'adv.在外面 n.外面 adj.外部的 prep.在 ... 外边', '1. The house is painted green outside. 那房子外面漆的绿色。 2. The outside of it looks all right. 它的外观还可以。 3. He has a rough outside but a good heart. 他外表粗鲁，但心地善良。 4. One should not judge a thing by the outside. 不能从外表来判断事物。 5. He isolated himself from the outside world. 他把自己与外部世界隔绝了。 6. He stood outside the house before going in. 他在进去之前曾站立在那屋子的外边。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accent', '[\'æksent]', 'n.重音；口音；强调 vt.重读；强调', '1. The accent falls on the third syllable. 重音落在第三个音节上。 2. She spoke with an Irish accent. 她说话带有爱尔兰口音。 3. He flattered himself that he spoke French with a perfect accent. 他自以为他说法语的腔调很完美。 4. The Government put the accent on light industry. 政府注重轻工业。 5. Please accent the first syllable. 请重读第一个音节。', '过去式: accented 过去分词: accented 现在分词: accenting 第三人称单数: accents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('red', '[red]', 'adj.红色的 n.红色', '1. I received a bunch of red roses on my birthday. 生日那天，我收到一束红玫瑰。 2. The dying fire was throwing out a dull red light. 将要熄灭的火发出暗红色的光。 3. Red squirrels are now very rare in Britain. 红色的松鼠在英国已十分罕见了。 4. The sky slowly changed from blue to red. 天空慢慢由蓝色变为红色。', '副词: redly 比较级: redder 最高级: reddest 名词: redness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('distant', '[\'dɪstənt]', 'adj.疏远的；遥远的；远房的；陌生的；远行的', '1. His stepson is still very distant towards him. 他的继子对他仍然很疏远。 2. Her manner was cold and distant. 她的态度冷漠而疏远。 3. It snows all the year round in that distant little village. 在那个遥远的小村落里整年下雪。 4. This palmer came from a very distant place. 这个朝圣者来自非常远的地方。', '副词: distantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ripe', '[raɪp]', 'adj.成熟的；熟的', '1. The branches were weighed down with ripe apples. 苹果成熟了把树枝都压弯了。 2. Most tomatoes are red when ripe, but some kinds are yellow. 大多数西红柿成熟时是红色的，但有些品种是黄色的。 3. The ripe apples picked easily. 成熟的苹果易于采摘 4. The time was ripe for a challenge to the power of the government. 时机已经成熟，可以向政府权力提出挑战了。', '副词: ripely 比较级: riper 最高级: ripest 名词: ripeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consolidate', '[kən\'sɒləˌdeɪt]', 'v.合并；统一；巩固', '1. The two companies consolidated last year. 这两个公司去年合并了。 2. We will consolidate and deliver together then. 我们届时将提前统一运输。 3. He bribes his leader to consolidate his position. 他贿赂他的领导来巩固他的地位。 4. We\'ve made a good start, now it\'s time to consolidate. 我们有了一个良好的开端, 现在应该加以巩固。', '名词: consolidator 过去式: consolidated 过去分词: consolidated 现在分词: consolidating 第三人称单数: consolidates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('splash', '[splæʃ]', 'n.溅泼（声）；溅泼的量；溅污的斑点；骚动；少许 v.溅（湿）；报道', '1. There was splash in the pond, and a big goldfish bobbed up. 水池里扑通一声，一条大金鱼窜了起来。 2. He jumped into the water with a splash. 他噗通一声跳进水里。 3. There\'s a splash of paint on the white wall. 白墙上溅上了一片油漆。 4. He achieved a perfectly clean entry,and there is almost no splash. 他的入水非常漂亮，几乎没有溅起水花。 5. The boys always splash about in rainwater. 孩子们总是在雨水里玩耍。', '名词: splasher 过去式: splashed 过去分词: splashed 现在分词: splashing 第三人称单数: splashes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yourself', '[jɔːr\'self]', 'pron.你(们)自己；你(们)亲自', '1. Forget yourself and think of someone else for a change. 别光想著你自己，你也为别人想一次。 2. Please make yourself at home. 请别客气。 3. You\'ve only yourself to blame. 你只能怪你自己。 4. Please don\'t blame yourself. 请不要责怪你自己。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('persuasion', '[pər\'sweɪʒn]', 'n.说服；劝说；信念', '1. Mr. Abel needed no more remonstrance or persuasion. 阿伯尔少爷再不需要什么劝告或说服了。 2. His father was reached by their persuasion at last. 他的父亲最后终于被他们说服了。 3. After a lot of persuasion, she agreed to go. 经过多次劝说后，她同意去了。 4. He was sweetened by her persuasion. 在她的劝说下他变得心平气和了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('congratulation', '[kənˌgrætʃə\'leɪʃən]', 'n.祝贺；恭喜', '1. May we proffer you our congratulations? 请让我们向你表示祝贺。 2. Please give him my congratulations when you see him. 请见到他时转达我的祝贺。 3. I sent her a gift as a token of my congratulation. 我给她寄去一件礼物表示祝贺。 4. We must telephone our congratulations to the happy couple. 我们得打电话向那对幸福的夫妻表示祝贺。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('classical', '[\'klæsɪkl]', 'adj.古典的；权威的；传统的；正统的', '1. Beethoven is regarded as one of the immortals of classical music. 贝多芬被认为是不朽的古典音乐大师。 2. Some young people like pop music, while still others like classical music. 一些年青人喜欢流行音乐，但仍有其它人喜欢古典音乐。 3. He is regarded as one of the classical composers in this century. 他被认为是本世纪第一流的作曲家之一。 4. The classical approach could be realized in at least two forms. 传统的道路被认为至少有两种形式。', '副词: classically 名词: classicality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wish', '[wɪʃ]', 'v.希望；想要 n.愿望；命令；渴望；祝颂（表达这个意思时，常用复数）', '1. If possible, I wish to work in sales department. 如果可能的话,我希望在销售部工作。 2. I wish you a good journey. 祝你一路平安。 3. Do you wish to say anything? 你想要说什么吗？ 4. His wish to be an actor has come true. 他想当演员的愿望实现了。', '名词: wisher 过去式: wished 过去分词: wished 现在分词: wishing 第三人称单数: wishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('novelty', '[\'nɑːvlti]', 'n.【C】新奇；小装饰 n.【U】新奇的事物；新奇的经验', '1. The novelty of his surroundings soon wore off. 他对环境的新奇感不久就淡薄了。 2. The demand is for quality, variety and novelty. 现在需求的是质量、花式品种和新颖性。 3. I bought some novelties on the boardwalk. 我在海滨人行道上买了一些新颖的小玩意儿。 4. Upon the whole the novelty attracted him. 总的说来，这个新奇的事物吸引着他。', '名词复数: novelties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hardly', '[\'hɑːrdli]', 'adv.几乎不；简直不；刚刚', '1. Hardly anybody came. 几乎没有人来。 2. He could hardly refrain himself. 他几乎不能自制。 3. The desert air contains hardly any moisture. 沙漠的空气几乎不含一点湿气。 4. He is so excited that he can hardly sleep. 他如此兴奋，几乎不能入睡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('departure', '[dɪ\'pɑːrtʃər]', 'n.出发；离开；分歧；新的尝试', '1. We made our departure in the early morning. 我们一大早就起程了。 2. All the arrangements should have been completed prior to our departure. 全部安排都应该在我们出发之前完成。 3. Her arrival coincided with our departure. 她来到时我们正好离开。 4. Her sudden departure has disarranged my plans. 她突然离去打乱了我的计划。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('particular', '[pər\'tɪkjələr]', 'adj.特定的；专指的；特殊的；特别的；挑剔的 n.详情；细节', '1. They depend on a particular historical situation. 它们取决于特定的历史境况。 2. I have nothing particular to do this evening. 今晚我没有什么特殊的事要做。 3. Clouds must be given a particular attention. 必须对云给予特别的注意。 4. She\'s very particular about what she wears. 她对衣著很讲究。 5. The account is correct in every particular. 所述的每一细节都正确无误。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('linear', '[\'lɪniər]', 'adj.直线的；长度的；线性的', '1. Students do not always progress in a linear fashion. 学生不会总是顺着一条直线进步。 2. The flow is linear, with some iterations in the planning phase. 过程流程是直线的，在计划阶段会有一些迭代。 3. He\'s making linear measurements. 他正在进行长度测量。 4. Not all types of motions are linear in character. 并非所有类型的运动在性质上都是线性的。', '副词: linearly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('directory', '[də\'rektəri]', 'n.目录；工商名录；指南 adj.给予指导的', '1. He thumbed through the directory to look for her number. 他翻阅电话号码簿找寻她的号码。 2. He found their address in the telephone directory. 他在电话薄里找到了他们的住址。 3. And here is our service directory. 这是服务指南。', '名词复数: directories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('magnify', '[\'mæɡnɪfaɪ]', 'v.放大；夸大', '1. I want to magnify my mother\'s picture. 我想放大我母亲的照片。 2. Magnify the magnitude of the magnetism. 放大磁性的大小。 3. He is inclined to magnify difficulties. 他老是爱夸大困难。 4. These groups and individuals magnify hate crimes by blacks in order to back their social agenda. 这些团体和个人为了给自己提出的社会议题造舆论而极力夸大黑人的攻击性犯罪。', '过去式: magnified 过去分词: magnified 现在分词: magnifying 第三人称单数: magnifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flag', '[flæɡ]', 'n.旗；旗帜；信号旗 vt.(以旗子)标出 v.无力地下垂；减退；枯萎', '1. Flags are fluttering in the breeze. 旗子在风中飘扬。 2. The flag was flown at half-staff. 那旗帜降了半旗。 3. The flag was aflutter in the air. 旗帜在空中飘扬。 4. The signal flag is fully in our sight from this position. 我从这个位置完全可以看到信号旗。 5. Halfway through the race he began to flag. 赛跑到一半他开始有点跑不动了。', '名词: flagger 过去式: flagged 过去分词: flagged 现在分词: flagging 第三人称单数: flags');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pace', '[peɪs]', 'n.速度；步伐；(一)步 v.踱步；(用步)测；(马)溜蹄走 prep.用在人名前(礼貌的表达不同意见)', '1. She works so fast that I can\'t keep pace with her. 她工作得很快，我跟不上她的速度。 2. When John found he was going to be late, he stepped up his pace. 约翰发现要迟到了, 就加大步伐。 3. They pace in sleek chivalric certainty. 自信的步态骑士般孔武而自如。 4. The trot is a pace of the horse. 快步是马行的一种步态。 5. The lion paced the floor of his cage restlessly. 狮子烦躁地在兽笼里走来走去。', '过去式: paced 过去分词: paced 现在分词: pacing 第三人称单数: paces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('air', '[er]', 'n.空气；天空；空中；感觉；神态；曲调；装腔作势 v.晾干；使通风；广播', '1. The fresh air in the morning made him feel glad. 早晨的新鲜空气使他觉得愉快。 2. There is a bird flying through the air. 一只小鸟从天空飞过。 3. The archers sent their shafts through the air. 弓箭手向空中射出利箭。 4. There was an air of excitement at the meeting. 开会时气氛显得有些兴奋。 5. You should air the clothes to get the damp out. 你应该把衣服晾一下去去潮气。', '过去式: aired 过去分词: aired 现在分词: airing 第三人称单数: airs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quiz', '[kwɪz]', 'n.恶作剧；测验；问答比赛 v.盘问；对 ... 进行测验', '1. I hate the quiz someone made. 我讨厌别人搞恶作剧。 2. We will have a quiz tomorrow morning. 我们明天早晨进行一个小测验。 3. He asked us to prepare for a quiz. 他要我们准备好测验。 4. Match your skill against the experts in this quiz. 在这一测验中你与专家较量一下技巧吧。 5. Four men are being quizzed by police about the murder. 警察就这起谋杀案正在盘问四个男子。', '名词: quizzer 名词复数: quizzes 过去式: quizzed 过去分词: quizzed 现在分词: quizzing 第三人称单数: quizzes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('installation', '[ˌɪnstə\'leɪʃn]', 'n.安装；装置；军事驻地', '1. We provide free delivery and installation. 我们免费送货和安装。 2. The price of these product will just compensate the cost of equipment and installation of the line. 你方生产的产品价格将正好补偿我方提供的设备及安装生产线的费用。 3. All large ships now have a wireless installation. 所有的大型船舶现在都有无线电装置。 4. The building was turned into a secret military installation. 这座建筑被变成了秘密军事设施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('substantial', '[səb\'stænʃl]', 'adj.大量的；坚固的；实质的；可观的 n.本质；重要部份', '1. New economic development policies led to substantial and rapid growth. 新的经济发展政策带来了快速和大量的增长。 2. Those workers have built many substantial buildings in the recent years. 近几年那些工人建造了许多坚固的建筑。 3. The reforms have made substantial headway. 改革取得了实质的进展。 4. The article is devoid of substantial matter. 这篇文章缺乏实质性的内容。', '副词: substantially 名词: substantiality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('symptom', '[\'sɪmptəm]', 'n.症状；征兆', '1. Cigarettes can aggravate the symptoms of a cold. 抽烟会加重感冒症状。 2. The doctor made his diagnosis after studying the patient\'s symptoms. 医生研究病人的症状后, 作出诊断。 3. Fever is a symptom of many illnesses. 发烧是许多疾病的症兆。', '形容词: symptomless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('identification', '[aɪˌdentɪfɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.确认；鉴定；识别；身份的证明', '1. A line of people is formed for identification. 人们排成一行等待确认身份。 2. He gave a positive identification of the killer. 他明确的认出了凶手。 3. Jewellery identification is a hard job. 珠宝鉴定不是一件容易的工作。 4. Fingerprint identification is widely used. 指纹鉴定被广泛运用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mysterious', '[mɪ\'stɪriəs]', 'adj.神秘的；不可思议的', '1. The enchanter is very mysterious. 魔法师非常神秘。 2. Africa is a mysterious land to him. 对他来说，非洲是一片神秘的土地。 3. We must pay special attention to the mysterious stranger. 我们必须对那个神秘的陌生人严加注意。 4. There are many mysterious stories about the Egyptian pyramids. 关于埃及金字塔有许多神秘的故事。', '副词: mysteriously 名词: mysteriousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('struggle', '[\'strʌɡl]', 'vi.努力；奋斗；斗争；挣扎 n.斗争；竞争；奋斗', '1. He struggled to control his temper. 他努力控制住自己的脾气。 2. They should therefore unite to struggle together. 因此,他们要联合起来,共同努力奋斗。 3. Let\'s join hands and struggle together. 咱们携起手来共同斗争。 4. People struggle at the dead-line. 人们在死亡线上挣扎。 5. He gave up the struggle in despair. 他绝望地放弃了斗争。', '副词: strugglingly 名词: struggler 过去式: struggled 过去分词: struggled 现在分词: struggling 第三人称单数: struggles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flight', '[flaɪt]', 'n.飞行；航班；镖尾；逃走，逃离，溃逃', '1. She photographed the birds in flight. 她拍摄鸟儿飞行的照片。 2. I\'ll book a direct flight to London for you. 我将为你预订直飞伦敦的航班。', '过去式: flighted 过去分词: flighted 现在分词: flighting 第三人称单数: flights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('playground', '[\'pleɪɡraʊnd]', 'n.操场；运动场；游乐场', '1. The students are playing on the playground. 学生们正在操场上玩。 2. The children were taking turns on the slides in the playground. 孩子们在操场上轮流滑滑梯。 3. He sat on the playground listening to the distant croak. 他坐在操场上，聆听远处的蛙鸣。 4. There are more than five hundred people on the playground. 运动场上有五百多人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('subscribe', '[səb\'skraɪb]', 'vt.订阅；签名；支持；捐赠；同意', '1. I subscribe to\" Reader\'s Digest\" magazine. 我订了《读者文摘》杂志。 2. They refused to subscribe to the agreement. 他们拒绝在协议上签字。 3. Do you subscribe to her pessimistic view of the state of the economy? 你是否同意她对经济状况所持的悲观看法？ 4. We subscribe to an animal protection society. 我们定期捐款给一个动物保护基金会。', '名词: subscriber 过去式: subscribed 过去分词: subscribed 现在分词: subscribing 第三人称单数: subscribes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('divide', '[dɪ\'vaɪd]', 'vt.划分；隔开；分割；[数]除 vi.分裂；分开 n.分水岭；分歧；分', '1. White lines divide the playing area into sections. 这些白线把赛区分成各个部分。 2. I hope this disagreement will not divide us. 我希望我们不会因这分歧而对立起来。 3. Divide the cake into equal parts. 把蛋糕分成等份。 4. Six divided by two is three. 六除以二得三。 5. Class differences can divide a nation. 阶级差异会造成国家的分裂。 6. This led to a divide between the upper class and the common man that persists to a degree down to the present generation. 这导致上层社会和平民大众之间的隔阂，在某种程度上，这个隔阂持续到当代。', '形容词: dividable 过去式: divided 过去分词: divided 现在分词: dividing 第三人称单数: divides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('courtesy', '[\'kɜːrtəsi]', 'n.礼貌；好意', '1. They showed us every courtesy. 他们对我们彬彬有礼。 2. Bill did me the courtesy of answering the question. 比尔很有礼貌地回答我的问题。 3. Thank you very much for your courtesy. 承蒙您的好意，甚为感谢。 4. Not to do so would show a lack of courtesy. 不这样做就会有失礼之嫌。', '名词复数: courtesies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cloak', '[kloʊk]', 'n.斗蓬；宽大外衣；掩盖物 v.遮掩；隐匿', '1. Dracula appeared, draped in a huge cloak. 吸血鬼披著一件大斗篷走了出来。 2. She picked up the old brown cloak and handed it to him. 她拎起棕色的斗蓬递给他。 3. He was muffled in a cloak. 他裹在大衣里。 4. The snow covered up the fields with a white cloak. 积雪给田野盖上了一件白色的外衣。 5. The appearance of good will cloak a sinister intention. 友善的外表掩盖了阴险的企图。', '过去式: cloaked 过去分词: cloaked 现在分词: cloaking 第三人称单数: cloaks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hence', '[hens]', 'adv.因此；从此以后', '1. It is very late; hence you must go to bed. 时间已经很晚了，因此你必须睡觉去。 2. It\'s handmade and hence expensive. 这是手工做的, 因此很贵。 3. I fell off my bike yesterday hence the bruises. 我昨天骑自行车摔倒了--所以青一块、 紫一块的。 4. The sports meet will be held three days hence. 运动会在三天后举行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reckon', '[\'rekən]', 'v.计算；认为；估计', '1. Did you reckon in the cost of the taxi? 你把出租车费算进去了吗？ 2. You should reckon in the cost of fuel. 你应当把燃料费计算在内。 3. They reckon the book as one of his best works. 他们认为这本书是他的优秀作品之一。 4. The news won\'t worry her, I reckon. 我看这消息不会使她不安。', '过去式: reckoned 过去分词: reckoned 现在分词: reckoning 第三人称单数: reckons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('total', '[\'toʊtl]', 'adj.总的；全体的；完全的 n.总数；合计 v.共计；总计', '1. The total cost will be 126 dollars. 总的费用要126美元。 2. You can choose four out of the total number. 你可以从全部数目中选出四个。 3. A dingle monthly total is posted to Accounts Receivable and Fees Earned in the general ledger. 全体的小峡谷月刊被寄到帐户应收帐款和费用在一般的分类帐中赚。 4. The news comes as a total surprise. 我得说这个消息来得太突然了。 5. Their expenses reached a total of 1,000 pounds. 他们的花费总计一千英镑。 6. Your debts total one thousand pounds. 你的债务共计为一千镑。', '过去式: totaled/totalled 过去分词: totaled/totalled 现在分词: totaling/totalling 第三人称单数: totals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unemployment', '[ˌʌnɪm\'plɔɪmənt]', 'n.失业；失业人数', '1. Mass unemployment may lead to social upheaval. 大批失业会导致社会动乱。 2. The specter of unemployment haunted the land. 失业的恐怖笼罩全国。 3. The decrease in unemployment was 30 percent. 失业人数减少了百分之三十。 4. One deals with unemployment claims. 一个涉及到失业人数情况。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thermal', '[\'θɜːrml]', 'adj.热的；热量的；保热的 n.上升的热气流', '1. An improved thermal head boosts image quality. 经过改进的热敏头,提高了图像质量。 2. The thermal energy has become more and more important. 热能变得越来越重要了。 3. These are thermal units. 这是热量单位。 4. My mother has bought the thermal underwear for me. 我妈妈已经给我买了保暖内衣。 5. While flying, you feel a weak thermal. 当飞行中，你感觉到一个微弱的热气流。', '副词: thermally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flat', '[flæt]', 'adj.平坦的；扁平的；单调的；断然的；[音乐]降音的；气不足的 adv.平直地；直截了当；低于标准音高地 n.<英>公寓；平面部分；[音乐]降半音；泄气轮胎 v.变平；降调；住公寓', '1. Most of our county is as flat as a pancake. 我们县大部分地方非常平坦。 2. In flat open country there is plenty of grass for the cattle to feed on. 在开阔平坦的地区有大量的青草供牛群食用。 3. People used to think that the earth was flat. 过去人们认为地球是扁平的。 4. He spoke in a flat monotone. 他说话单调低沉。 5. She lay flat on her back in the warm sunshine. 她在温暖的阳光下平躺著。 6. She is buying a flat close to her office. 她正在购买一套靠近她办公室的单元房。', '副词: flatly 比较级: flatter 最高级: flattest 名词: flatness 过去式: flatted 过去分词: flatted 现在分词: flatting 第三人称单数: flats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('challenge', '[\'tʃælɪndʒ]', 'n.挑战；邀请比赛；盘问；质疑 v.向 ... 挑战；盘问；质疑', '1. The crossing of this dangerous river was a challenge to most of us. 对我们大多数人来说,横渡这条充满危险的大河确实是个挑战。 2. He accepted his friend\'s challenge to swim across the river. 他接受朋友提出的挑战，游过这条河。 3. We accepted their challenge to a baseball game. 我们接受了他们棒球邀请的挑战。 4. He ignored the sentry\'s challenge to halt. 他不理睬哨兵喝令止步的盘问。 5. Nowadays no one will challenge the fact that the earth is round. 现在没有人会对地球是圆的这一事实提出异议。', '形容词: challengeable 过去式: challenged 过去分词: challenged 现在分词: challenging 第三人称单数: challenges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jam', '[dʒæm]', 'n.果酱 n.堵塞；拥挤；困境 v.塞满；挤；卡住；夹伤；干扰；猛压', '1. He spread some apple jam on the bread. 他在面包上涂上苹果酱。 2. I reached across the table for the jam. 我伸手到桌子那端去拿果酱。 3. Traffic jams in the town happen everyday. 城里的交通天天堵塞。 4. We were delayed in a traffic jam. 我们因交通拥挤而迟到了。 5. The holiday traffic is jamming the roads. 假日的车辆堵塞了交通。', '形容词: jammable 名词: jammer 过去式: jammed 过去分词: jammed 现在分词: jamming 第三人称单数: jams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invite', '[ɪn\'vaɪt]', 'vt.邀请；请求；招致；招待', '1. I\'ve invited the Smiths round for drinks next Friday. 我已邀请史密斯一家下周五来家中小酌。 2. We invited all our relatives to the wedding. 我们邀请了所有的亲戚来参加婚礼。 3. After his speech he invited questions and comments(from the audience). 他讲完话后请听众提出问题和意见。 4. His policies invited widespread criticism. 他的政策招致广泛的指责。', '过去式: invited 过去分词: invited 现在分词: inviting 第三人称单数: invites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('produce', '[prə\'duːs]', 'v.生产；引起；提出；制片；分娩 n.产品；农产品', '1. This tree produces rubber. 这些树生产橡胶。 2. It is certain that we shall produce this kind of engine. 毫无疑问,我们将生产这种发动机。 3. The plain weave is comparatively inexpensive to produce. 相对来说,平纹组织的生产成本较低。 4. His announcement produced gasps of amazement. 他宣布的消息引起了一片惊叹声。 5. This shop sells native produce. 这家商店出售土特产品。', '形容词: producible 过去式: produced 过去分词: produced 现在分词: producing 第三人称单数: produces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scar', '[skɑːr]', 'n.疤痕；伤痕；断崖 v.结疤；痊愈', '1. He has a scar running across his left cheek. 他左脸上有一道很长的疤痕。 2. The scar flawed her beauty. 这伤疤损害了她的美貌。 3. The cut in her hand has healed completely, without leaving a scar. 她手上的刀伤完全愈合了,没有留下一点伤痕。 4. In that heart, where there had been a wound, there was a scar. 在他的心上，从前有过一条伤口，后来只剩下一条伤痕。 5. The wound gradually scarred over. 伤口渐渐愈合。', '过去式: scarred 过去分词: scarred 现在分词: scarring 第三人称单数: scars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('riot', '[\'raɪət]', 'n.暴乱；骚乱；喧闹；（色彩）丰富；<俚>有趣的人 v.闹事；骚乱', '1. The military were called in to deal with the riot. 已将军队调来镇压暴乱。 2. The outbreak of riot caused many people to die. 暴乱的发生使很多人丧生。 3. The police stopped several riots on election night. 警方在竞选之夜制止了几处骚乱。 4. Football hooligans ran riot through the town. 闹事的足球迷在城里胡作非为。 5. He fermented prejudiced crowds to riot. 他煽动有偏见的群众起来闹事。', '名词: rioter 过去式: rioted 过去分词: rioted 现在分词: rioting 第三人称单数: riots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('predict', '[prɪ\'dɪkt]', 'v.预言；预报；预知；预测', '1. It is virtually impossible to predict the future accurately. 精确预言未来的事实际上是办不到的。 2. The economists predicted an increase in the rate of inflation. 经济学家预言通货膨胀率将会增长。 3. The earthquake had been predicted several months before. 这次地震早在几个月以前就发布了预报。 4. It is impossible to predict what will happen. 预知未来的事是不可能的。', '形容词: predictable 副词: predictably 名词: predictability 过去式: predicted 过去分词: predicted 现在分词: predicting 第三人称单数: predicts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('repression', '[rɪ\'preʃn]', 'n.抑制；压抑；镇压', '1. The repression of one\'s true feelings is wrong. 抑制自己的真实情感是不对的。 2. His goal was the repression of insolence. 他的目标是抑制傲慢的态度。 3. His repression broke out. 他的压抑终于爆发了。 4. The repression of your true feelings is harmful to your health. 压抑你的真实感情有害健康。', '形容词: repressionist');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thrust', '[θrʌst]', 'v.刺；插入；推挤 n.刺；推力；要旨', '1. The mugger thrust at his victim with a knife. 抢劫者用刀子向受害人刺去。 2. The murderer killed her by thrusting a knife in her back. 凶手把刀刺进她的背部，杀害了她。 3. He thrust his hands into his pockets. 他把两手插入衣袋里。 4. We thrust our way through the crowd. 我们用力挤过人群。 5. The fencer parried his opponent\'s thrust. 击剑手挡开了对手的猛刺。', '形容词: thrustful 名词: thruster 过去式: thrust 过去分词: thrust 现在分词: thrusting 第三人称单数: thrusts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eloquent', '[\'eləkwənt]', 'adj.雄辩的；有口才的；动人的', '1. He addressed the audience in an eloquent speech. 他向听众发表了雄辩的演说。 2. Eloquent elephants telephoned other eloquent elephants. 雄辩的大象打电话给其他雄辩的大象。 3. Such an eloquent man will easily talk us down. 这样一个有口才的人很容易把我们驳得无话说。 4. An eloquent speaker is one skilled in the use of words. 有口才的人善于用词。', '副词: eloquently 名词: eloquentness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('foot', '[fʊt]', 'n.脚；英尺；最底部；音步 v.表演舞步；步行；付账；踏；共计', '1. I apologized to her for stepping on her foot. 我因踩了她一脚向她道歉。 2. I hurt my foot while playing football. 在踢足球时,我的脚受伤了。 3. They sank the post two feet deep in the ground. 他们把这根柱子在地下埋了两英尺深。 4. I missed the target by one foot. 我差一英尺就击中目标。 5. We foot it all the night. 我们跳了一整夜的舞。', '名词复数: feet 过去式: footed 过去分词: footed 现在分词: footing 第三人称单数: foots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ought', '[ɔːt]', 'aux.应该；应当；本该 n.<古>零', '1. I don\'t think you ought to. 我看你不应该。 2. You ought to be more careful, you know. 你应该小心一点，知道吗？ 3. The information ought to be made more accessible. 资料应该明白易懂。 4. You ought to scrap the old bike and buy a new one. 你应该扔掉这辆旧自行车，买一辆新的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('snowstorm', '[\'snoʊstɔːrm]', 'n.暴风雪；雪暴', '1. The snowstorm added to our difficulties. 暴风雪增加了我们的困难。 2. All the traffic was tied up by the snowstorm. 所有的交通都因暴风雪停顿了。 3. The snowstorm swept the vast expanse of grassland. 暴风雪袭击了辽阔的草原。 4. I couldn\'t visit him, what with the snowstorm and the cold I had. 由于暴雪,加上我感冒,我无法去拜访他。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('east', '[iːst]', 'adj.东方的 adv.向东方 n.东方；东部', '1. Take the east road, it\'s the shortest way. 走东边这条路吧,这是最近的路。 2. He traveled east. 他向东旅行。 3. China is in the east of the world. 中国位于世界的东方。 4. The sun rises in the east and sets in the west. 太阳从东方升起，在西方落下。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('would', '[wʊd]', 'aux.将；可能；大概；总会；愿意；will的过去式', '1. The president proclaimed that a new currency would be issued. 总统宣布将发行新货币。 2. He would have lost his position if you hadn\'t backed him up. 假如你当初没有支持他,他可能已经失去职位了。 3. It would take about 30 minutes. 大概要开30分钟。 4. Every time he saw me, he would say hello to me. 每当他看见我,总向我问好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('highly', '[\'haɪli]', 'adv.高度地；很；非常；赞许地', '1. These procedures are highly irregular. 这些程序是很不合乎规则的。 2. His style is offbeat but highly creative. 他的风格很不寻常但非常有创造力。 3. We have to admit that he\'s a highly competent man. 我们必须承认他是个非常能干的人。 4. His style is offbeat but highly creative. 他的风格很不寻常但非常有创造力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('top', '[tɑːp]', 'n.顶部；顶；上面；极点；陀螺 adj.最高的；顶端的 vt.形成顶部； 达到…的顶端； 处于…的最前头 vi.总结； 超越； 高耸； 结束', '1. The mountain tops are covered with snow. 白雪覆盖着山顶。 2. The staircase was short, and they were soon at the top. 梯子是短的,他们一下子就到了顶上。 3. The green book is at the bottom of the pile and the red one is on top. 绿皮书在那一堆书的底下，红皮书在上边。 4. He worked his way to the top of his profession. 他一步一步努力，终于成为行业内的翘楚。 5. I live on the top floor. 我住在顶层。', '过去式: topped 过去分词: topped 现在分词: topping 第三人称单数: tops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shout', '[ʃaʊt]', 'v.呼喊；高声呼叫 n.呼喊；大声叫', '1. He opened his mouth to shout, but no sound came out. 他张开嘴呼喊,但是没有发出声音。 2. He didn\'t shout, he just glared at me silently. 他没有喊叫，只是默默地怒视着我。 3. The children on the sand were shouting with excitement. 沙滩上的孩子们兴奋得大喊大叫。 4. The crowd shouted the speaker down. 群众高声喊叫把演讲人的声音压了下去。 5. Her warning shout came too late. 她发出的警告呼喊声来得太晚了。', '名词: shouter 过去式: shouted 过去分词: shouted 现在分词: shouting 第三人称单数: shouts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quench', '[kwentʃ]', 'v.熄灭；结束；冷淬；解渴', '1. Water will quench a fire. 水可以灭火。 2. Nothing could quench her longing to return home again. 她重返家园的念头怎么也打消不掉。 3. Hot steel is quenched to harden it. 烧热的钢淬火使它坚硬。 4. Her sarcastic remarks quenched his passion. 她讽刺的话冷却了他的热情。', '形容词: quenchable 名词: quencher 过去式: quenched 过去分词: quenched 现在分词: quenching 第三人称单数: quenches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hotel', '[hoʊ\'tel]', 'n.旅馆；饭店；宾馆；酒店', '1. This is the identical hotel we stayed at last year. 这就是我们去年住过的旅馆。 2. The front of the postcard shows a picture of our hotel. 明信片正面是我们旅馆的图片。 3. We stayed at a small hotel. 我们住在一家小旅馆里。 4. I have engaged a room at this hotel. 我已经在这个旅馆里预订了一个房间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('channel', '[\'tʃænl]', 'n.频道；海峡；方法；通道；（消息）渠道 vt.引导；形成河道；集中（精力）', '1. This channel comes on the air every morning at 7 am. 这个频道每天早晨7点钟开始播放。 2. The ship went through the English Channel fast. 那条船很快的通过了英吉利海峡。 3. She was seeking a channel for her creative energies. 她正在为她创造性的能量寻找方法。 4. We can reach these markets through our existing distribution channels. 我们可以通过我们现有的分散渠道到达这些市场。 5. All information on the classes is channeled through the principal\'s office. 课上的所有信息都被传到校长办公室了', '名词: channeler 过去式: channeled/channelled 过去分词: channeled/channelled 现在分词: channeling/channelling 第三人称单数: channels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('presence', '[\'prezns]', 'n.出席；存在；到场；【生】存在度', '1. We shall be very glad to have your presence. 你如能出席,我们将感到很高兴。 2. She was so quiet that her presence was hardly noticed. 她那么安静，几乎没有人注意到她在这里。 3. He made believe not to be aware of my presence. 他假装不知道我在那里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hello', '[hə\'loʊ]', 'int.(打招呼)喂；你好', '1. Hello, it\'s me. 喂，是我呀。 2. Hello, it\'s us back again! 喂，是我们回来了！ 3. Say hello to your husband. 问你的丈夫好。 4. I said hello to her, but she ignored me completely! 我向她打招呼，可她根本不理我！', '异体字: hullo 名词复数: hellos 过去式: helloed 过去分词: helloed 现在分词: helloing 第三人称单数: helloes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('severe', '[sɪ\'vɪr]', 'adj.严厉的；严重的；剧烈的；严格的；严峻的', '1. The premier came under severe criticism. 这位总理遭到严厉的抨击。 2. He\'s suffering from severe mental disorder. 他患有严重的精神病。 3. A severe storm turned the small village down to ground. 一场剧烈的风暴把小村夷为平地。 4. The new product has stood a severe proof . 新产品经受了严格的考验。', '副词: severely 比较级: severer 最高级: severest 名词: severeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('carpenter', '[\'kɑːrpəntər]', 'n.木匠 v.做木工活', '1. The carpenter was busy sawing the logs into planks. 这位木匠正忙着把圆木锯成厚板。 2. The carpenter flung aside all his tools in a rage. 木匠怒气冲冲地将工具扔在一边。 3. The carpenter told me how to use a bevel. 木匠告诉我怎样用斜角规。 4. My uncle carpentered a table and a few stools for his needy neighbor. 我叔父给他穷困的邻居做了一张桌子和几只凳子。', '名词: carpentry 过去式: carpentered 过去分词: carpentered 现在分词: carpentering 第三人称单数: carpenters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('moisture', '[\'mɔɪstʃər]', 'n.水分；潮气；湿度', '1. The plants absorb moisture from the soil. 植物从土壤中吸取水分。 2. The sun will take the moisture out of the clothes. 太阳光会把衣服上的水分蒸发掉。 3. If you air your quilt on such a wet day, it\'ll soak up the moisture. 如果在这么潮湿的天晒被子，被子就会把湿气都吸去。 4. Amounts of moisture in soil vary greatly. 土壤中湿度变化很大。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('massive', '[\'mæsɪv]', 'adj.巨大的；大量的；大规模的；大范围的；严重的', '1. A massive boulder blocked the entrance of the cave. 一块巨大的圆石堵住了山洞的入口。 2. We have seen massive changes in recent years. 这几年我们经历了巨大的变化。 3. The soldier suffered a massive haemorrhage and died soon after. 那个战士经受了大量出血的痛苦，不久便去世了。 4. We must make massive efforts to improve things. 我们必须作出极大的努力去改善一切。', '副词: massively 名词: massiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transplant', '[\'trænsplænt]', 'v.移居；移栽(植物)；移植(器官) n.移植；移植物', '1. The villagers will transplant to another place. 村民们将移居到另外一个地方。 2. The peasants bent over to transplant rice seedlings in the fields. 农民们在地里弯腰插秧。 3. It is now possible to transplant organs from animals into people. 现在将动物身上的器官移植入人体内已经成为了可能。 4. The doctors will transplant a human heart into the patient. 医生们将把一颗人的心脏移植到这个病人身上。 5. I think the heart transplant is a wonderful thing. 我认为心脏移植是件神奇的事。', '形容词: transplantable 名词: transplantation 过去式: transplanted 过去分词: transplanted 现在分词: transplanting 第三人称单数: transplants');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coke', '[koʊk]', 'n.焦炭 n.<口>可口可乐(=Coca-Cola) v.（使）炭化', '1. Coke consists mainly of carbon. 焦炭的主要成分是碳。 2. Without coke iron cannot be smelted. 没有焦炭就不能炼铁。', '过去式: coked 过去分词: coked 现在分词: coking 第三人称单数: cokes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('northwest', '[\'nɔːθ\'west]', 'n.西北；西北方 adj.西北的；在西北的；来自西北的 adv.向西北', '1. There is a large hilly area in the northwest. 西北部有一大片丘陵地带。 2. The city is located in the northwest part of Canada. 这座城市位于加拿大的西北部。 3. The park is northwest from the city. 公园在该市的西北。 4. A cold wind blew from northwest. 冷风从西北方向吹来。 5. The tourists drove northwest. 游客们开车向西北而去。', '形容词: northwestern');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disclose', '[dɪs\'kloʊz]', 'vt.揭露；使某物显露；公开', '1. I have no intention of disclosing their names. 我无意泄露他们的姓名。 2. The Government disclosed that another diplomat has been arrested for spying. 政府透露 3. The violets disclose their petals. 紫罗兰绽开花瓣。 4. Science can disclose the mysteries of nature. 科学能解开自然界的奥秘。', '形容词: disclosable 名词: discloser 过去式: disclosed 过去分词: disclosed 现在分词: disclosing 第三人称单数: discloses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dead', '[ded]', 'adj.死的；不起作用的；无趣的；筋疲力尽的；麻木的；完全的；无效的；沉闷的；（指球）界外的 adv.完全地；直接地；突然地', '1. It lay there with its eyes closed, dead as a doornail. 它躺在那里眼睛闭著，确实死了。 2. He has been dead for two years. 他已死了两年。 3. The phone went dead. 电话打不通了。 4. The battery is dead. 电瓶没电了。 5. He was dead asleep. 他酣然大睡。', '比较级: deader 最高级: deadest 名词: deadness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nearly', '[\'nɪrli]', 'adv.几乎；差不多；密切地', '1. Nearly all of them kept aloof from such doctrines. 他们几乎都不接受这种教条。 2. That fever nearly finished him off. 那场热病几乎送了他的命。 3. He plays golf nearly every weekend. 他差不多每个周末都打高尔夫球。 4. They sat so close that their heads nearly touched. 他们坐得那么近，头都差不多碰到一起了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('noble', '[\'noʊbl]', 'adj.高贵的；宏伟的；高尚的 n.贵族', '1. These few words fully revealed her noble quality. 这寥寥数语充分显示了她的高贵品质。 2. Jim is descended from a noble family. 吉姆出身于一个贵族家庭。 3. The noble peaks tower into the clouds. 壮丽的山峰高耸入云。 4. His noble example inspired the rest of us to greater efforts. 他那高尚的榜样激发我们大家更加努力。 5. It was said that he was from a noble family. 据说他出身于贵族家庭。', '副词: nobly 比较级: nobler 最高级: noblest 名词: nobleness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('terrify', '[\'terɪfaɪ]', 'v.使害怕；使恐怖；威胁', '1. Or will carelessness or corruption allow the theft of a nuclear device to terrify us all? 会不会由于安全部门的疏忽或腐败，让恐怖分子得到核装置用来威胁民众？', '过去式: terrified 过去分词: terrified 现在分词: terrifying 第三人称单数: terrifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stereo', '[\'sterioʊ]', 'adj.立体声的；有立体视觉的 n.立体声；固定形象', '1. Who originated the concept of stereo sound? 立体声是谁发明的？ 2. We\'re being deafened by next door\'s stereo. 隔壁的立体声音响要把我们耳朵震聋。 3. This is no time to lash out on a new stereo. 现在不是奢侈花钱买新立体音响的时候。', '名词复数: stereos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('insert', '[ɪn\'sɜːrt]', 'v.插入；嵌入 n.插入物', '1. She inserted the key into the lock. 她把钥匙插入锁中。 2. You can insert additional pages into that book. 你可以把附加的散页插入那本书里。 3. The next procedure is to insert the battery. 接下来的步骤是装进电池。 4. He tried to insert an advertisement in a newspaper. 他设法将广告刊登在报纸上。 5. She found an insert in the book. 她在那本书中找到了一个插入物。', '名词: inserter 过去式: inserted 过去分词: inserted 现在分词: inserting 第三人称单数: inserts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('habit', '[\'hæbɪt]', 'n.习惯；习性', '1. He is in the habit of rising early. 他有早起的习惯。 2. I have to bear with his bad habit. 我不得不忍受他的坏习惯。 3. My colleague has broken off the habit of smoking. 我的同事已经戒掉了吸烟的习惯。 4. He has a habit of sunbathe for two hours a day. 他习惯每天做两小时日光浴。', '过去式: habited 过去分词: habited 现在分词: habiting 第三人称单数: habits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pencil', '[\'pensl]', 'n.铅笔；笔状物 vt.用铅笔写', '1. He erases pencil marks. 他擦去铅笔的痕迹。 2. My pencil is blunt, could you lend me a knife to sharpen it? 我的铅笔钝了，你能借我把刀子削一削吗？ 3. I noted down his telephone number with a pencil near the telephone. 我用电话旁的一根铅笔记下了他的电话号码。 4. He took a pencil flashlight out of his pocket. 他从口袋中掏出一支笔形电筒。 5. He penciled down his name on a piece of paper. 他在一张纸上用铅笔写下了自己的名字。', '名词: penciler 过去式: penciled/pencilled 过去分词: penciled/pencilled 现在分词: penciling/pencilling 第三人称单数: pencils');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('foster', '[\'fɔːstər]', 'vt.领养；培养；促进；鼓励；抱有（希望等） adj.收养的', '1. People who cannot have a baby of their own sometimes foster (a child). 不能生育的人有时领养别人的(孩子). 2. It is very important to foster an interest. 培养一种兴趣是十分重要的。 3. The mother tried to foster her son\'s interest in music. 母亲设法培养儿子对音乐的兴趣。 4. Ignorance fosters superstition. 无知助长迷信。 5. The foster children also deserve love and care. 收养的孩子也应该得到关爱。', '过去式: fostered 过去分词: fostered 现在分词: fostering 第三人称单数: fosters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('maneuver', '[mə\'nuːvər]', 'vt.巧妙地操纵；使演习；调遣 vi.演习；调遣；用计策 n.演习；策略；调遣', '1. The mouse had a quick wit and was able to maneuver his way out of danger. 老鼠有急智可以灵巧地脱离危险。 2. They have had to maneuver the ship to avoid unforeseen shoals and shallows. 他们必须设法避开无法预见的暗礁和浅滩。 3. The maneuver aims to strengthen special police forces\' emergency response and combat capabilities. 此次演习的目的在于提高特种警力的危机反应能力和战斗能力。 4. An anti-failure maneuver is very important for power system safety and stability in operation. 反事故演习是保证电网安全稳定运行的重要一环。 5. He must have considered the patrol as an effective maneuver. 他思想上一定还以为派兵侦察是条妙计。', '形容词: maneuverable 名词: maneuverability 过去式: maneuvered 过去分词: maneuvered 现在分词: maneuvering 第三人称单数: maneuvers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('platform', '[\'plætfɔːrm]', 'n.月台；讲台；平台；站台；(政党的)政纲', '1. Any train from this platform stops at Gatwick. 从这一月台开出的火车都在盖特威克停。 2. He was walking up and down the station platform. 他在火车站的月台上走来走去。 3. Jane walked boldly up to the platform without faltering. 简沉著大胆地走上讲台。 4. A balcony is a platform with a wall. 阳台是有墙的平台。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('circle', '[\'sɜːrkl]', 'n.圆圈；圈子；包厢 v.划圈；包围；盘旋；环绕', '1. The dancers were standing in a circle around the fire. 舞者们围着篝火站成一圈。 2. A square has four sides but a circle has no sides. 正方形有四条边，而圆形没有边。 3. He has a large circle of friends. 他有一大群朋友。 4. He is part of an exclusive social circle and belongs to an exclusive club. 他所处的社交圈子很排外，而且参加的又是个很排外的社团。 5. Someone had circled the next paragraph in red. 有人将下一段划了一个红圈。', '名词: circler 过去式: circled 过去分词: circled 现在分词: circling 第三人称单数: circles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fisherman', '[\'fɪʃərmən]', 'n.渔夫；渔船', '1. The fisherman transfixed the shark with a harpoon. 渔夫用鱼叉刺住鲨鱼。 2. With dredging , the fisherman tows a chain mesh behind a fishing boat in order to scoop up sea life from the seabed. 利用拖捞网，渔人在渔船后面拖动一串筛网，从而从海床捞起海洋生物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clockwise', '[\'klɑːkwaɪz]', 'adj.顺时针方向的 adv.顺时针方向地', '1. It may whirl either clockwise or counterclockwise. 它可能顺时针方向或反时针方向旋转。 2. Regulation is accomplished by rotating the handwheel clockwise. 规则要求按顺时针方向旋转手轮。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arrange', '[ə\'reɪndʒ]', 'vt.整理；安排；计划；改编(乐曲) vi.协商；计划', '1. You must arrange these books in alphabetical order. 你要把这些书按字母顺序排好。 2. I have arranged one of my staff to meet you at the airport. 我已经安排好一个职员到飞机场接你。 3. If you can arrange the tourist destinations for me, I will be very grateful. 如果你能为我计划一下,我将不胜感激。 4. I have arranged with the neighbours about taking care of the cat. 我已和邻居们商量好照顾猫咪的事情。', '名词: arranger 过去式: arranged 过去分词: arranged 现在分词: arranging 第三人称单数: arranges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Marxist', '[\'mɑːksɪst]', 'adj.马克思主义的 n.马克思主义者', '1. We must study history from a Marxist viewpoint. 我们必须用马克思主义的观点研究历史。 2. They were fanatical Marxist communists. 他们是狂热支持马克思主义的共产主义者。 3. That kind of person is anything but a Marxist. 那种人根本不是马克思主义者。 4. There he became first a Darwinist, then a Marxist. 然后，他先是变成了达尔文主义者，接着又成了马克思主义者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beg', '[beɡ]', 'v.恳求；乞讨 abbr.开始(=begin)', '1. She begs them not to punish her son severely. 她恳求他们不要给他儿子太重的处罚。 2. The boys hailed passing cars to beg a ride. 这些男孩向过往的汽车呼叫恳求乘车。 3. He knew he had hurt her and begged her to forgive him. 他自知伤了她的心而央求她原谅。 4. He lives by begging. 他以行乞为生。', '过去式: begged 过去分词: begged 现在分词: begging 第三人称单数: begs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rational', '[\'ræʃnəl]', 'adj.合理的；理性的；能推理的 n.有理数', '1. Your choice was perfectly rational under the circumstances. 在那种情况下,你的选择是相当合理的。 2. Man is a rational being. 人是有理性的生物。 3. No rational person would go to work in his pyjamas. 任何神智正常的人都不会穿着睡衣去上班。 4. The rational numbers also fit into this scheme. 有理数也适用于这个图形。', '副词: rationally 名词: rationalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('subordinate', '[sə\'bɔːrdɪnət]', 'adj.下级的；次要的 n.属下；附属物 vt.使服从；把 ... 放在次要', '1. He is a subordinate officer. 他是位下级军官。 2. She works in the subordinate hospital of our universtiy. 她在我们学校的附属医院工作。 3. All the other issues are subordinate to this one. 所有问题都要以这个问题为主。 4. He was always friendly to his subordinates. 他对下级一向和蔼可亲。 5. He subordinated his wishes to the general good of the group. 他使自己的愿望服从于集体的利益。', '形容词: subordinative 副词: subordinately 名词: subordinateness 过去式: subordinated 过去分词: subordinated 现在分词: subordinating 第三人称单数: subordinates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bottom', '[\'bɑːtəm]', 'n.底部；底端 adj.底部的 v.触底；打(基础)', '1. There are tea leaves in the bottom of my cup. 我的杯底有茶叶。 2. They sent the enemy ship to the bottom of the sea. 他们把敌舰击沉。 3. He was always bottom of the class in maths. 他的数学成绩在班上总是垫底。 4. Put your books on the bottom shelf. 把你的书放在最下层的架子上. 5. There is no sign that the recession has bottomed out yet. 没有迹象表明萧条已经到了极点。', '名词: bottomer 过去式: bottomed 过去分词: bottomed 现在分词: bottoming 第三人称单数: bottoms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thrive', '[θraɪv]', 'vi.兴旺；繁荣；茁壮成长', '1. A business cannot thrive without good management. 没有良好的经营管理，事业就不会兴旺发达。 2. But will they survive and thrive? 但是，他们会生存下来并兴旺繁殖吗? 3. May our country prosper and thrive forever! 希望我们的国家繁荣兴旺，长盛不衰。 4. A business can not thrive without investment. 没有投资任何生意都无法繁荣。', '名词: thriver 过去式: thrived/throve 过去分词: thrived/thriven 现在分词: thriving 第三人称单数: thrives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('facilitate', '[fə\'sɪlɪteɪt]', 'vt.促进；帮助；使 ... 容易', '1. Friendly contacts between different peoples facilitate the cultural and economic interchange. 各国人民的友好接触促进文化和经济交流。 2. We facilitate them to resist the enemy. 我们帮助他们与敌人对抗。 3. The new underground railway will facilitate the journey to all parts of the city. 新的地下铁路将为去城市各处提供方便。', '形容词: facilitative 名词: facilitator 过去式: facilitated 过去分词: facilitated 现在分词: facilitating 第三人称单数: facilitates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lean', '[liːn]', 'v.倾斜；倾向；依靠；倚；屈身 adj.瘦的；贫乏的；无脂肪的 n.瘦肉；倾斜，倾向', '1. The trees leant in the wind. 树在风中倾斜。 2. Kids today lean toward casual clothes. 今天的孩子倾向于穿随便的衣服。 3. I lean towards letting him go alone. 我倾向于让他一个人去。 4. We lean on our friends when we are in trouble. 我们遇到困难时依靠朋友帮助。 5. The little girl only eats lean pork. 这个小女孩只吃瘦肉。', '副词: leanly 比较级: leaner 最高级: leanest 名词: leanness 过去式: leaned 过去分词: leaned 现在分词: leaning 第三人称单数: leans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('such', '[sʌtʃ]', 'adj.这样的；如此的 adv.如此地 pron.这样的人或事；其本身；这；那', '1. He said he hadn\'t got time or made some such excuse. 他说他没有时间, 或是找诸如此类的借口。 2. Such a disaster as her car being stolen had never happened before. 有的祸事，像她的汽车被盗之类，以前从未发生过。 3. He had never before gazed on such splendour. 他生平从未见过如此壮观的场面。 4. I\'ve never seen such beautiful scenery. 我从没见过这样美丽的景色。 5. He did not oppose the scheme as such. 他并不反对那项方案本身。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tonight', '[tə\'naɪt]', 'adv.今晚 n.今晚', '1. The band is really in the groove tonight. 乐队今晚演奏得精彩极了。 2. We have a leg of mutton for dinner tonight. 我们今晚有只羊腿作晚餐。 3. The theme for tonight\'s talk is education. 今天谈话的题目是教育。 4. We have a leg of mutton for dinner tonight. 我们今晚有只羊腿作晚餐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prophet', '[\'prɑːfɪt]', 'n.预言者；先知', '1. Once in a while, the prophet indulges in fantasy. 偶尔，那个预言家会纵情于幻想。 2. A prophet made a prophecy that the kingdom would fall. 一位预言家预言那个王国将要灭亡。 3. The prophet said that war will break out. 先知预言战争将爆发。 4. No man is a prophet in his own country. 先知在自已家乡从来不被认可。', '名词: prophethood');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('equation', '[ɪ\'kweɪʒn]', 'n.相等；均衡；方程式；等式', '1. The equation of wealth with happiness can be dangerous. 把财富与幸福等同起来是很危险的 2. I can\'t make this equation come out. 我不会解这个方程式。 3. What does x represent in this equation? 这个方程式中的x代表什么? 4. The professor wrote an equation on the blackboard. 教授在黑板上写了一个等式。', '形容词: equational 副词: equationally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('I', '[aɪ]', 'pron.我', '1. I don\'t like bananas. 我不喜欢香蕉。 2. I didn\'t hurt you, did I? 我没有伤害你,是吧？ 3. It is I who will suffer. 我将是那个要受苦的人。 4. I enjoy the book very much. 我非常喜欢那本书。', '名词复数: i\'s');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('board', '[bɔːrd]', 'n.木板；布告板；董事会；船舷或机舱；伙食；舞台 v.登(飞机、车、船等)；接受乘客；有偿提供食宿；搭伙；用木板覆盖', '1. Will you draw the nails from this board? 请你把钉子从这块木板上拔出来好吗? 2. Paste down the map on the board. 把这张地图用浆糊贴在布告板上。 3. Her election to the board of directors caused great surprise. 她被选进董事会,令人大为吃惊。 4. Please get on board at once; the plane is taking off very soon. 请即刻登机；飞机马上就要起飞了。 5. Passengers must board the ship by 6 p.m. 旅客必须在下午六点钟以前上船。', '过去式: boarded 过去分词: boarded 现在分词: boarding 第三人称单数: boards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('certainly', '[\'sɜːrtnli]', 'adv.当然；一定', '1. You are certainly a talented artist. 你当然是位有天赋的艺术家。 2. I\'ll certainly be most discreet in my conversation. 我在谈话中当然会十分小心的。 3. He will certainly come. 他一定会来的。 4. He\'ll certainly die if you do not send for a doctor right now. 如果你不马上请医生,他一定会死的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('smooth', '[smuːð]', 'adj.光滑的；平稳的；流畅的；圆滑的；可口的；安祥的；均匀的 v.使光滑；消除；安慰；理顺(羽毛)', '1. Her skin is as smooth as silk. 她的皮肤像丝绸一样光滑。 2. The birch has smooth bark and slender branches. 桦树有光滑的皮和细长的枝。 3. At 9:50 the plane began a smooth descent through the cloud-smudged sky to Shanghai. 9点50分,飞机在上海上空开始穿过浓云平稳下降。 4. The process of negotiation was not entirely smooth. 谈判的过程并不十分顺畅。 5. She smoothed out wrinkles out of the tablecloth. 她把桌布上的皱褶弄平。', '副词: smoothly 比较级: smoother 最高级: smoothest 名词: smoother 过去式: smoothed 过去分词: smoothed 现在分词: smoothing 第三人称单数: smoothes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('descendant', '[dɪ\'sendənt]', 'n.后裔；子孙；后代', '1. He is a descendant of Queen Victoria. 他是维多利亚女王的后裔。 2. I am a descendant of George Washington. 我是乔治华盛顿的后代子孙。 3. A static method does not change when inherited by a descendant class. 当被子孙类继承时，静态方法并不改变。 4. The coastal areas were occupied by the descendants of Greek colonists. 沿海地带居住着希腊殖民者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flock', '[flɑːk]', 'n.一群；兽群；大堆；群众；羊群 v.聚集；成群而行', '1. There are many flocks of tourists in the palace. 宫殿里有好几群游客。 2. A flock of sheep poured through the gate. 一群羊从羊圈口涌了出来。 3. People came in flocks to see the royal procession. 人们蜂拥而至瞻望皇室人员外出时的仪仗队。 4. A few sheep have been lost from the flock. 羊群里少了几只羊。 5. Huge numbers of birds have flocked together by the lake. 成群的鸟聚集在湖畔。', '过去式: flocked 过去分词: flocked 现在分词: flocking 第三人称单数: flocks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('improve', '[ɪm\'pruːv]', 'vt.改善；改进；提高 vi.变得更好；改进', '1. Your work will get by, but try to improve it. 你的工作勉强通过了,但要设法改善它。 2. He offered a suggestion to improve the plan. 他提出一个建议,以改进那项计划。 3. I want to improve my English. 我想提高我的英语水平。 4. Wine improves with age. 酒存放得越久越醇。', '过去式: improved 过去分词: improved 现在分词: improving 第三人称单数: improves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strict', '[strɪkt]', 'adj.严格的；精确的；完全的', '1. Our manager is very strict with us. 我们的经理对我们要求很严格。 2. There are strict controls on immigration into this country. 移民到这个国家有严格的限制。 3. Anything you tell us is in the strictest confidence. 你告诉我们的都是绝密信息。 4. Don\'t worry about that; he is a man with strict loyalty. 不用担心那一点,他是一个绝对忠诚的人。', '副词: strictly 比较级: stricter 最高级: strictest 名词: strictness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('traffic', '[\'træfɪk]', 'n.（人或车等）交通流量；不正当生意（走私） v.做生意（多指违法的）；游览', '1. Traffic reaches a peak between 8 and 9 in the morning. 早晨八九点钟是交通的高峰时刻。 2. His left knee was hurt in a traffic accident. 他的左膝在一次交通事故中受伤了。 3. There\'s usually a lot of traffic at this time of day. 每天在这段时间往来车辆都很多。 4. Drug traffic on city streets is a big problem. 在大街上非法进行毒品交易是个大问题。 5. He trafficked in illicit liquor. 他做过买卖私酒的生意.', '名词: trafficker 过去式: trafficked 过去分词: trafficked 现在分词: trafficking 第三人称单数: traffics');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consult', '[kən\'sʌlt]', 'v.查阅；请教；商讨；就诊', '1. I will have to consult the plane time table first. 我得先查阅飞机时刻表。 2. He paused to consult his notes, and then proceeded with his questions. 他停下来看了看笔记，然后继续提问。 3. If you wish good advice, consult an old man. 若要主意好，老人须请教。 4. I need to consult with my colleagues on the proposals. 我需要和我的同事商讨这些建议。', '名词: consulter 过去式: consulted 过去分词: consulted 现在分词: consulting 第三人称单数: consults');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unless', '[ən\'les]', 'conj.除非；如果不 prep.除 ... 外', '1. I won\'t go to the party unless I\'m invited. 除非我被邀请，否则我不会去参加晚会的。 2. I sleep with the window open unless its really cold. 我总是开著窗户睡觉，除非天气非常冷才关上窗户。 3. Iron corrodes unless it is greased or kept clean. 如果不涂油或保持清洁铁便会腐蚀。 4. Unless you work harder, you will not pass the examination. 如果不加紧用功，你就不能通过考试。 5. Nothing could stop me from waiting for you to come back unless death. 除了死亡再没有别的事物能够阻止我等待你回来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('immune', '[ɪ\'mjuːn]', 'adj.免疫的；免除的', '1. This patient\'s immune system has been destroyed. 这位病人的免疫系统受到了破坏。 2. I\'m immune to smallpox as a result of vaccination. 我接种过疫苗了,所以对天花有免疫力。 3. Nobody is immune from criticism. 谁都难免受批评。 4. The criminal was told he would be immune if he helped the police. 这个罪犯被告知，如果他协助警方就可以免于被起诉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tablet', '[\'tæblət]', 'n.药片；匾；片状物；平板电脑', '1. Fill a glass with water and dissolve this tablet in it. 倒杯水把药片放进去溶解了。 2. The doctor told him to take two tablets of aspirin before every meal. 医生告诉他每天饭前吃两片阿斯匹林。 3. On the tablet are the Roman numerals for July 4, 1776. 匾上的罗马数字写着1776年七月四日。 4. The son fixed a tablet to the wall in menmory of his father. 儿子在墙上挂了一片匾来纪念父亲。', '过去式: tableted 过去分词: tableted 现在分词: tableting 第三人称单数: tablets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shabby', '[\'ʃæbi]', 'adj.破旧的；寒酸的；低劣的，无耻的；卑劣的', '1. He owns nothing beyond the shabby house. 除了那个破旧的房子,他一无所有。 2. His shabby appearance creates a bad impression. 他那寒酸的样子给人留下不好的印象。 3. She is none the less beautiful for her shabby clothing. 即使她衣衫褴褛，却仍然美丽。 4. His reasoning is weak, even shabby. 他的论证软弱无力，甚至可以说很拙劣。', '副词: shabbily 比较级: shabbier 最高级: shabbiest 名词: shabbiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impair', '[ɪm\'per]', 'vt.损害；削弱 [计算机] 损伤.', '1. Loud noise would impair your hearing. 大的噪音会损害你的听觉。 2. Smoking can impair the sexual response. 抽烟可以削弱性反应。 3. His illness has impaired his efficiency. 生病降低了他的效率。 4. Don\'t boil the sauce as this and impair the flavor. 酱汁还要煮沸，否则会影响味道。', '名词: impairment 过去式: impaired 过去分词: impaired 现在分词: impairing 第三人称单数: impairs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('graze', '[ɡreɪz]', 'v.放牧；（牛、羊等）吃草 v.轻擦；擦伤 n.放牧 n.擦伤', '1. We are grazing the sheep in the next field. 我们在旁边的地里放羊。 2. The sheep usually graze in the grass land. 羊通常在草地吃草。 3. Cattle are not allowed to graze in the plots. 禁止牛在田里吃草。 4. The bullet grazed my shoulder. 子弹擦过我的肩膀。 5. Cows are left to graze in the pasture. 奶牛都是留给放牧在牧场。 6. His knee stung from the graze. 他的膝盖擦伤后十分疼痛。', '形容词: grazeable 名词: grazer 过去式: grazed 过去分词: grazed 现在分词: grazing 第三人称单数: grazes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('modernization', '[ˌmɒdənaɪ\'zeɪʃn]', 'n.现代化', '1. China is advancing towards modernization. 中国正在向现代化进军。 2. International competition was a spur to modernization. 国际竞争是实现现代化的动力。 3. The modernization of the industry was phased over a 20-year period. 工业现代化分20年逐步实现。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loyalty', '[\'lɔɪəlti]', 'n.忠诚；忠心；忠贞', '1. His loyalty is above suspicion. 他的忠诚无可置疑。 2. My judgement was frequently faulty, but my loyalty to the nation could not be questioned. 我的判断经常出错，但是我对祖国的忠诚是无可置疑的。 3. You can\'t put a price on that sort of loyalty. 那样的忠心是不能用金钱来衡量的。 4. Loyalty to the former king still persists in parts of the country. 该国一些地方仍有人忠于前国王。', '名词复数: loyalties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('petroleum', '[pə\'troʊliəm]', 'n.石油', '1. Indonesia is abundant in petroleum deposits. 印尼的石油蕴藏量丰富。 2. Petroleum can be used to produce various chemical products. 石油可用于生产多种化学产品。 3. Any new source of energy will be welcome, as there is a shortage of petroleum. 由于石油短缺，任何一种新能源都会受欢迎。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blend', '[blend]', 'v.混合 n.混合物', '1. Oil does not blend with water. 油不溶於水。 2. The sea and the sky seemed to blend into each another. 大海和蓝天似乎连成了一片。 3. The poem blends the separate ingredients into a unity. 这首诗把几个分开的部分融合为一体。 4. The curtains blend in perfectly with the furniture. 窗帘(的颜色)跟家具(的颜色)十分和谐。 5. Which blend of coffee would you like? 你要哪一种混合咖啡?', '过去式: blended/blent 过去分词: blended/blent 现在分词: blending 第三人称单数: blends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sheep', '[ʃiːp]', 'n.绵羊；羊；羊皮', '1. Can you distinguish goat from sheep? 你能把山羊和绵羊区分开吗？ 2. The dog that molested the sheep was killed. 那只骚扰绵羊的狗被杀死了。 3. The sheep are lambing this week. 这个星期绵羊要产羔。 4. Will the hedge keep the sheep out of the field? 这篱笆能将羊群挡在田地外面吗？', '名词复数: sheep');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('delegate', '[\'delɪɡeɪt]', 'n.代表 v.派 ... 为代表；委派；授权；委托', '1. Babbitt was an official delegate. 巴比特是一名正式代表。 2. He was elected as a delegate to the annual conference. 他被选为年会代表。 3. He can\'t delegate command. 他不能委派代表来指挥。 4. You can\'t do all the jobs yourself---you can delegate a task to your subordinate. 你不能包揽所有的工作---你可以把任务委派给下属。', '名词: delegator 过去式: delegated 过去分词: delegated 现在分词: delegating 第三人称单数: delegates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resort', '[rɪ\'zɔːrt]', 'n.(度假)胜地；手段；凭借 vi.诉诸；常去', '1. The island is a favorite summer resort for tourists. 这座岛是旅游者的避暑胜地。 2. Its unique natural scenery makes it an ideal holiday resort. 独具特色的自然景观,使这里成为度假休闲的理想胜地。 3. A carriage was the only resort. 乘马车是唯一的办法。 4. The resort to force is forbidden in this school. 该学校禁止动武。 5. If other means fail，we shall resort to force. 如果其他手段均失败,我们就将诉诸武力。', '过去式: resorted 过去分词: resorted 现在分词: resorting 第三人称单数: resorts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loose', '[luːs]', 'adj.松的；宽松的；不确切的；不牢固的；放纵的 n.解放；放任；放纵 v.弄松；释放；放枪 adv.松散地', '1. The screw worked itself loose and the door fell off the cupboard. 螺丝松了，门从橱柜上掉下来了。 2. She wore loose garments in the summer. 她在夏天穿宽松的衣服。 3. Loose labour regulations are one reason. 宽松的劳动规则是原因之一。 4. It is used these days in a very loose sense by a great many people. 现在,许多人用起它来是很不确切的。 5. This will ship to our customer via their consolidator as loose freight. 这将会经由他们的整合者对我们的客户运送如解放船货。 6. Please help me loose the nail, It is rusty and won\'t come out of the wall. 请帮我把这个钉子弄松，它生锈了，拔不出来。', '副词: loosely 比较级: looser 最高级: loosest 名词: looseness 过去式: loosed 过去分词: loosed 现在分词: loosing 第三人称单数: looses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prose', '[proʊz]', 'adj.散文的 n.散文', '1. This is a verbal translation of the prose. 这是那篇散文的逐字直译。 2. He has lately set forth a book on prose. 他最近出版一本论散文的著作。 3. His prose is written in elegant language. 他的散文写得十分优雅。 4. I want to glance over one time this piece of prose. 我想浏览一下这篇散文。', '过去式: prosed 过去分词: prosed 现在分词: prosing 第三人称单数: proses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dominate', '[\'dɑːmɪneɪt]', 'v.支配；控制；统治；占优势；俯视；高耸于', '1. That way, he can dominate the game. 那样他才能支配比赛。 2. He desires to dominate over others. 他很想支配别人。 3. He has authority, but he doesn\'t try to dominate (others). 他有权威 4. They had the ambition to dominate this small country. 他们有控制这个小国的野心。', '形容词: dominative 名词: dominator 过去式: dominated 过去分词: dominated 现在分词: dominating 第三人称单数: dominates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('radius', '[\'reɪdiəs]', 'n.半径范围；半径；桡骨；辐射区', '1. Nobody is allowed to enter the operation radius. 不允许任何人进入工作半径范围以内。 2. What is the radius of this circle? 这个圆的半径有多长? 3. We can compute the circular area with radius. 我们能用半径计算出圆的面积。 4. The radius expands markedly at its lower end. 桡骨下端明显扩张。', '名词复数: radii');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('historic', '[hɪ\'stɔːrɪk]', 'adj.有历史意义的；历史的', '1. This battle is of historic meaning. 这一战具有历史意义。 2. China\'s takeover of Hong Kong was a historic event. 中国收回香港是一件具有历史意义的大事。 3. The small symbols on this map denote historic places and museums. 这个地图上的小记号表示史迹兴博物馆。 4. The historic strike gave an enormous impetus to the whole American labor movement. 这次历史性的罢工对整个美国的劳工运动起了很大的推动作用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bow', '[baʊ]', 'n.弓；鞠躬礼；蝴蝶结；船头 v.鞠躬；致敬；压弯', '1. At that time, people hunt with bows and arrows. 在那时,人们以弓﹑ 箭行猎。 2. He moved aside for her with a polite bow. 他礼貌地鞠躬，退避一旁让她过去。 3. She has a dress decorated with bows. 她有一条饰有蝴蝶结的连衣裙。 4. My little sister can tie shoelaces in a bow. 我妹妹能把鞋带打成蝴蝶结。 5. The cast bowed as the audience applauded. 演员们向鼓掌的观众鞠躬。', '过去式: bowed 过去分词: bowed 现在分词: bowing 第三人称单数: bows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('uncle', '[\'ʌŋkl]', 'n.伯；姑父；舅；叔；姨父', '1. My uncle is a professor in this university. 我的伯父是这所大学的一名教授。 2. They are not really my aunt and uncle. 其实他们并不是我的姑姑和姑父。 3. My uncle is a sure-enough cowboy. 我舅舅是个地道的牛仔。 4. My uncle has an apple orchard. 我叔叔拥有一个苹果园。', '形容词: uncleless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('select', '[sɪ\'lekt]', 'v.选择；挑选 adj.精选的；优等的 n.被挑选出来的人或物', '1. Please select a channel to begin with from left. 请从左边选择一个频道。 2. She lets her son select his own Christmas present. 她让儿子自己选择圣诞礼物。 3. They select him to their leader. 他们选择他为他们的领导人。 4. She selected a diamond ring from the collection. 她从收藏品中挑选了一枚钻石戒指。 5. A select group were invited to the wedding reception. 一群经过挑选的人士被邀请参加婚宴。', '形容词: selectable 名词: selectness 过去式: selected 过去分词: selected 现在分词: selecting 第三人称单数: selects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('onion', '[\'ʌnjən]', 'n.洋葱', '1. I don\'t like the flavor of onion. 我不喜欢洋葱的味道。 2. This soup tastes strongly of onion. 这汤洋葱味太浓。 3. We had steak and fried onion for dinner. 我们晚餐吃牛排和炒洋葱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('condition', '[kən\'dɪʃn]', 'n.条件；情况 v.训练；决定；以 ... 为条件；护理（头发）', '1. Conditions in poor quarters were horrible. 城里穷人居住区条件十分糟糕。 2. I had halfway decided to accept their conditions at that time. 当时我已差不多决定要接受他们的条件了。 3. The terrorists will only release their hostage on certain condition. 恐怖分子只有在某些条件下才释放人质。 4. Jimmie had but a vague idea of world conditions now. 杰米对当今世界情况只有一点模糊的了解。 5. I conditioned the dog to bark at strangers. 我训练这只狗对陌生人吠叫。', '过去式: conditioned 过去分词: conditioned 现在分词: conditioning 第三人称单数: conditions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('erupt', '[ɪ\'rʌpt]', 'v.爆发；喷发；发疹', '1. Violence has erupted on the streets. 大街上突然发生了暴乱。 2. The demonstration erupted into violence. 示威游行中突然出现了武斗。 3. An active volcano may erupt at any time. 活火山随时可能喷发。 4. It\'s many years since Mount Vesuvius last erupted. 维苏威火山上一次喷发至今已有很多年了。', '形容词: eruptive 副词: eruptively 过去式: erupted 过去分词: erupted 现在分词: erupting 第三人称单数: erupts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('proud', '[praʊd]', 'adj.自豪的；自尊的；自傲的；壮观盛大的', '1. If your father had still been alive, he would have felt very proud of you. 你父亲如果还健在的话,他会为你骄傲的。 2. It was a proud day for us when we won the trophy. 我们夺得奖杯那一天是值得我们骄傲的日子。 3. They are poor but proud. 他们虽穷但很自重。 4. He\'s too proud to speak to poor people like us. 他太骄傲了,从不与我们这样的穷人说话。', '副词: proudly 比较级: prouder 最高级: proudest 名词: proudness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('joy', '[dʒɔɪ]', 'n.欢乐；喜悦；乐趣；[大写] 乔伊(女子名) v.高兴；喜悦', '1. He is in immeasurable joy. 他沉浸在巨大的欢乐之中。 2. I saw the joy in her smiling face. 从她的笑脸上我看到欢欣。 3. Tears of joy streamed down her face. 喜悦的泪水从她的脸上流下来。 4. Joy mingled with surprises. 喜悦和惊异交织在一起。 5. I joy to see you so successful. 我看到你如此成功而感到欣慰。', '过去式: joyed 过去分词: joyed 现在分词: joying 第三人称单数: joys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impressive', '[ɪm\'presɪv]', 'adj.给人深刻印象的', '1. His collection of paintings is the most impressive. 他的绘画收藏令人叹为观止。 2. The report looks impressive but it\'s really nothing but waffle. 这篇报告貌似冠冕堂皇，实际上空洞无物。 3. Among his many good qualities, punctuality is the most impressive one. 在他众多优秀品质中,守时给人留下了最深刻印象。 4. Their success is all the more impressive when you consider the efforts they\'ve made. 如果你考虑到他们所付出的努力,你就会觉得他们的成功真的很了不起。', '副词: impressively 名词: impressiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ebb', '[eb]', 'n.退潮；衰落 vi.落潮；衰退', '1. They started sailing on the ebb. 他们于退潮时出航了。 2. But the moments will never ebb away. 但那些瞬间永远不会退潮。 3. Private and public virtues were at the lowest ebb. 公德与私德均在衰落之中。 4. Manufacturing business is now at a low ebb. 制造业现正处于衰落中。 5. Fishing boats were standing down with the ebb. 渔船趁着落潮出航。', '过去式: ebbed 过去分词: ebbed 现在分词: ebbing 第三人称单数: ebbs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dispose', '[dɪ\'spoʊz]', 'v.清除；处理掉；解决；杀死；打败', '1. I want to dispose of these old books. 我想处理掉这些旧书。 2. Most complaints can be disposed of pretty quickly. 大多数投诉可以很快地解决。 3. The president ruthlessly disposed of his rivals. 这位总统无情地除掉了政敌。 4. She disposed of the champion in straight sets. 她一盘未输战胜了冠军。', '名词: disposer 过去式: disposed 过去分词: disposed 现在分词: disposing 第三人称单数: disposes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chat', '[tʃæt]', 'vi.闲谈；谈天 n.闲谈；聊天', '1. He came round last week and we chatted for a while. 上星期他顺道来访,我们闲谈了一会。 2. He likes to chat with his e-pals on the Internet. 他喜欢上网与网友聊天。 3. Ask him to stop by for a chat. 请他来坐坐，聊聊天。 4. It is pleasant to chat with friends, and with no chat is it more pleasant than with close friends. 和朋友聊天是愉快的，而这种情形没有比和知己的朋友聊天更为愉快。', '过去式: chatted 过去分词: chatted 现在分词: chatting 第三人称单数: chats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cabinet', '[\'kæbɪnət]', 'n.橱柜；内阁 adj.内阁的；秘密的', '1. She needs a cherry cabinet in her room. 她需要在她房里添一个樱桃木的柜子。 2. I put my collection of old glasses in the cabinet. 我把收集的古玻璃器皿放在橱里。 3. The question was discussed in cabinet. 在内阁会议上讨论了这个问题。 4. They have found out the mole in the cabinet. 他们已经发现了内阁中的间谍。 5. He was elevated to cabinet rank. 他被提升到内阁部长级。', '名词: cabinetful');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('indicate', '[\'ɪndɪkeɪt]', 'v.指示；象征；显示；暗示，预示 v.表明；指明', '1. This is used to indicate the temperature of the enclosure. 这个用来指示壳体的温度。 2. Sword indicates the bearer to a just and generous pursuit of honor and virtue in warlike deeds. 长剑象征剑的佩有者在格斗中具备公正、宽恕的美德。 3. My car\'s gas gauge indicated that there was little gas left. 我车上的汽油表显示剩下的油不多了。 4. His hesitation indicates unwillingness. 他的犹豫表明不愿意。', '形容词: indicatory 过去式: indicated 过去分词: indicated 现在分词: indicating 第三人称单数: indicates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('railroad', '[\'reɪlroʊd]', 'n.铁路；铁路公司 =railway（英）. vt.由铁道运输；使（议案等）草草通过；迫使仓促行事 vi.在铁路公司工作', '1. We will send the goods by railroad. 我们将用铁路运输货物。 2. The building of the railroad is progressing. 铁路正在建造中。 3. Butterfield\'s railroad lost some money. 巴特菲尔德的铁路公司损失了点钱。 4. These goods will be railroaded to that city. 这些货物将由铁路运送到那个城市。 5. Butterfield\'s railroad lost some money. 巴特菲尔德的铁路公司损失了点钱。', '名词: railroader 过去式: railroaded 过去分词: railroaded 现在分词: railroading 第三人称单数: railroads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('temperature', '[\'temprətʃər]', 'n.气温；体温；温度；发烧', '1. The temperature has stayed hot this week. 本周气温一直都很热。 2. The temperature soared to 43 degrees centigrade on July 25. 7月25日,气温猛升到4摄氏度。 3. After the storm there will be a sharp drop in temperature. 风暴过后,气温会骤降。 4. Let me take his (her) temperature and have a check. 我来给他(她)量一下体温,检查一下。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('minister', '[\'mɪnɪstər]', 'n.外交使节；部长；大臣；牧师 v.照顾；给予帮助', '1. The president gave his minister carte blanche in foreign affairs. 总统把处理外交事务的全权授予他的公使。 2. He was elected Minister of Education. 他被选为教育部长。 3. The minister can only act in this matter with the sanction of Parliament. 部长只有得到国会批准才能就此事采取行动。 4. The Chancellor of the Exchequer is the minister in charge of finance in Britain. 英国财政大臣是负责财政的大臣。 5. I have to minister to my mother all the time. 我不得不一直照料我的母亲。', '过去式: ministered 过去分词: ministered 现在分词: ministering 第三人称单数: ministers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dangerous', '[\'deɪndʒərəs]', 'adj.危险的；不安全的', '1. It is dangerous to walk on thin ice in a lake. 在湖中薄冰上行走是很危险的。 2. Dangerous driving should be severely punished. 危险驾驶应受严惩。 3. It is dangerous for you to stay here. 你呆在这儿不安全。', '副词: dangerously 名词: dangerousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drunk', '[drʌŋk]', 'adj.醉酒的；陶醉的 n.醉鬼；醉酒 动词drink的过去分词形式.', '1. He was obviously drunk. 他显然是醉了。 2. The drunk man lost his pouch in the bar. 那个喝醉了的人在酒吧里丢失了钱袋。 3. Men were drunk now with a kind of fury of contest. 现在人们在一种斗争的狂热中陶醉了。 4. Several drunks lay on the floor. 好几个醉汉躺在地板上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bug', '[bʌɡ]', 'n.臭虫；窃听器；[计]漏洞 v.窃听；打扰；失去(镇定)', '1. Why do we need bug spray? 我们要杀虫剂干什么? 2. The police tested the room for bugs. 警察检查房间里是否放有窃听器。 3. There might be a bug in the program. 程序里可能有一个错误。 4. Be careful what you say; our conversation may be being bugged. 说话要当心，咱们的话可能被窃听了。', '名词: bugger 过去式: bugged 过去分词: bugged 现在分词: bugging 第三人称单数: bugs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hang', '[hæŋ]', 'v.悬挂；(使)低垂；悬浮(在空中)；逗留；绞死 n.悬挂方式；悬挂；绞刑', '1. You may hang your coat on the hook. 你可以把外套挂在钩子上。 2. I\'ll hang the pictures as high as I can. 我将尽可能把这些画挂得高。 3. All the shirts hang together in the same wardrobe. 所有的衬衫都挂在同一个衣橱里。 4. Her hair hung long in the back. 她的头发长长地披在身后。 5. The hang of the curtain shows that somebody is standing behind it. 窗帘悬挂的样子表明有人站在后面。', '过去式: hung 过去分词: hung 现在分词: hanging 第三人称单数: hangs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beginning', '[bɪ\'ɡɪnɪŋ]', 'n.开始；开端；起源；早期 adj.刚开始的 动词begin的现在分词.', '1. The trees are just beginning to leaf. 树刚刚开始长叶子。 2. He was biased against the plan from the beginning. 他从一开始就对这个计划有偏见。 3. The knowledge of sin is the beginning of salvation. 认罪是得救的开端。 4. We have already made a good beginning. 我们已经有了一个良好的开端。 5. That’s why, in this beginning stage of my new habit, I\'ve been focusing on pleasure. 这就是为什么在我刚开始锻炼的时候，我总是把焦点放在锻炼的乐趣上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('considerate', '[kən\'sɪdərət]', 'adj.考虑周到的；体谅的；体贴的', '1. It was considerate of you to bring me my raincoat. 你为我带来雨衣,真是想得周到。 2. It is considerate of you to call on your relatives from time to time. 你时时拜望亲戚很周到啊。 3. He is no more considerate of others than his brother is. 他不体谅别人，就跟他弟弟一样。 4. She\'s a very considerate and caring person. 她是一个很懂得体贴和关心的人。', '副词: considerately 名词: considerateness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('senate', '[\'senət]', 'n.参议院；大学理事会', '1. The Senate confirms all treaties. 所有的条约都由参议院批准。 2. The Senate has voted to support the President\'s defense plans. 参议院已经投票支持总统的防卫计划。 3. The Senate resolved to accept the President\'s budget proposals. 参议院通过决议接受总统的预算建议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('leadership', '[\'liːdərʃɪp]', 'n.领导；领导才干', '1. He shows quality of leadership. 他显示出领导才能。 2. He was elected to the leadership of the Labour Party. 他被选为工党的领导人。 3. Several candidates had been manoeuvring for position long before the leadership became vacant. 领导职位尚未空缺，几个竞争者早就在为向上爬而钩心斗角了。 4. I\'ve learned a lot over the years and developed my leadership qualities. 这么多年来，我学会了很多东西，也发展了自己的一些领导才干。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sleep', '[sliːp]', 'v.睡觉 n.睡眠；睡觉', '1. I didn\'t sleep well last night. 昨晚我睡不安稳。 2. He have to sleep by day and work by night. 他只好白天睡觉，晚上工作。 3. He\'d been sleeping rough for a week, in ditches and haystacks. 他在沟里和草堆里露宿了一个星期。 4. I haven\'t had enough sleep lately. 最近我睡眠不足。', '过去式: slept 过去分词: slept 现在分词: sleeping 第三人称单数: sleeps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kid', '[kɪd]', 'n.小孩；年轻人；小山羊；小山羊皮制品 vi.(山羊等)下崽；捉弄 vt.开玩笑；哄骗；嘲弄 adj.较年幼的', '1. The kid dug a tunnel in the sand. 小孩在沙堆里挖了一个地道。 2. She sees me as a little kid who counts for nothing. 她认为我还是目个无足轻重的小孩子。 3. Half the kids round here are unemployed. 这里的年轻人有一半失业。 4. When he returned the kid was roasted. 当他回来的时候,小山羊已经烤熟了。 5. You\'re kidding! 你在开玩笑吧！ 6. He was trying to kid us about it. 他想拿那件事开我们玩笑。 7. His kid sister clerks in a store. 他妹妹在商店当店员。', '副词: kiddingly 名词: kidder 过去式: kidded 过去分词: kidded 现在分词: kidding 第三人称单数: kids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comic', '[\'kɑːmɪk]', 'n.连环图画；喜剧演员 adj.滑稽的；有趣的；喜剧的', '1. Children like to read comics. 孩子们喜欢看连环漫画。 2. He is looking for his comic book. 他在找他的连环画。 3. He is a popular TV comic. 他是观众喜爱的电视喜剧演员。 4. The comic scenes in the play were overdone. 这剧的滑稽场面太夸张了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skill', '[skɪl]', 'n.技能；技艺；技巧；熟练', '1. The crisis put his courage and skill to the test. 这次危难是对他的勇气和技能的考验。 2. She dealt with the problem with consummate skill. 她以巧妙的手腕处理了这个问题。 3. Resources management is an important business skill. 资源管理是一项重要的经营技能。 4. As a lightweight his skill is of the highest order. 作为轻量级拳击手，他的技术是第一流的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('March', '[mɑːrtʃ]', 'n.行军；行进；游行示威；稳步前进；进行曲 v.行进；前进；进发；使同行；游行示威 March n.三月', '1. Not a single man fell out in the long march. 在长途行军中没有一个人掉队。 2. The army was now on the march to Shanghai. 部队当时正向上海进军。 3. Science is on the march. 科学正在进步中。 4. The peace march attracted a large turnout. 和平游行吸引了大量的参加者。 5. The shower being over, we continued to march. 阵雨过去之后我们继续行进。 6. This term will begin on March 1st. 这个学期三月一日开始。', '过去式: marched 过去分词: marched 现在分词: marching 第三人称单数: marches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('religion', '[rɪ\'lɪdʒən]', 'n.宗教；宗教信仰', '1. He is a disciple of religion. 他是宗教信徒。 2. Jesus was the founder of the Christian religion. 耶稣是基督教的创始人。 3. Politics and religion are daily topics of conversation. 政治和宗教是人们平常交谈的主要话题。 4. There are many religions in the world. 世界上有许多种宗教信仰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hysterical', '[hɪ\'sterɪkl]', 'adj.歇斯底里的；异常兴奋的；<口>十分可笑的', '1. Janet became hysterical and began screaming. 珍妮特变得歇斯底里，开始尖叫。 2. His hysterical laughter made everybody stunned. 他那歇斯底里的笑声使所有的人不知所措。 3. He is hysterical at the sight of the photo. 他一看到那张照片就异常激动。', '副词: hysterically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hike', '[haɪk]', 'n.徒步旅行；远足；涨价 vi.远足；提高', '1. He always bring a canteen with him on a hike. 他作徒步旅行时总是带着水壶。 2. The storm upset their plans for a hike. 暴风雨破坏了他们的远足计划。 3. The government announced a 300 per cent hike in bread prices. 政府宣布面包涨价三倍。 4. He wants to hike round the world. 他打算徒步旅行环游世界一周。', '名词: hiker 过去式: hiked 过去分词: hiked 现在分词: hiking 第三人称单数: hikes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adore', '[ə\'dɔːr]', 'vt.爱慕；崇拜；很喜欢', '1. Men can only adore women who are adorable. 男人们只爱慕那些让人爱慕的女人。 2. The kids adore their father and confide in him. 孩子们崇拜并信赖他们的父亲。 3. The boys adore their mothers. 男孩们敬慕他们的母亲。 4. All the girls in our school adore the handsome mathematics teacher who happens to be a bachelor. 我们学校里所有女孩子都崇拜那个恰巧是单身汉的英俊数学老师。', '副词: adoringly 名词: adorer 过去式: adored 过去分词: adored 现在分词: adoring 第三人称单数: adores');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scarcely', '[\'skersli]', 'adv.几乎不；简直不；刚刚；决不', '1. He spoke scarcely a word of English. 他几乎连一个英文单词都不会说。 2. We scarcely ever used the reserve generator. 我们几乎从未用过这台备用发动机 3. This book is scarcely worthy reading. 这本书简直不值得阅读。 4. I could scarcely recognize him. 我简直认不出他来了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drag', '[dræɡ]', 'v.拖；拉；迫使；缓慢行进；进行过久；扯进；打捞 n.拖；拉；累赘；阻力 n.男子穿的女子服装', '1. He dragged the heavy case across the floor. 他在地板上拖着那个沉重的箱子。 2. shrug aside 不予理会 3. She dragged herself out of bed, still half asleep. 她挣扎着起了床,还是睡眼惺忪。 4. She always drags behind us. 她总是在我们后面吃力地跟着。 5. The cat is really excited by the drag of the basket on the floor. 在地板上来来回回拖着篮子可着实让那只猫兴奋了一回。', '过去式: dragged 过去分词: dragged 现在分词: dragging 第三人称单数: drags');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('haste', '[heɪst]', 'n.急速；急忙 v.匆忙；赶快', '1. The more haste, the less speed. 欲速则不达。 2. In his haste, he forgot to bring his glasses with him. 匆忙之中，他忘了带眼镜。 3. She made haste to open the door. 她急忙打开门。 4. They acted with precipitate haste. 他们鲁莽仓促地采取了行动。 5. We advised him against acting in haste. 我们劝他不要匆忙行事。', '过去式: hasted 过去分词: hasted 现在分词: hasting 第三人称单数: hastes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('experimental', '[ɪkˌsperɪ\'mentl]', 'adj.实验的；实验性的；试验性的', '1. The technique is still at the experimental stage. 这项技术正处于实验阶段。 2. The experimental results bear out our supposition. 实验结果证实了我们的假设。 3. The result obtain differ in different experimental method. 不同的试验方法所得到的结果也不同。 4. This is an experimental form of teaching. 这是一种实验性的教学形式。', '副词: experimentally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brochure', '[broʊ\'ʃʊr]', 'n.小册子，资料手册', '1. I\'ll send you a brochure. 我给你一份小册子。 2. The computer\'s features are detailed in our brochure. 该计算机的特点在我们的小册子中有详细介绍。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anxiety', '[æŋ\'zaɪəti]', 'n.焦虑；担心；渴望', '1. It proved difficult to disguise his anxiety. 他的焦虑难以掩饰。 2. They show great anxiety concerning their retirement allowance. 他们对自己的养老金问题显得十分焦虑。 3. This has caused us much anxiety. 这事使我们极为担心。 4. Some anxiety still lurked in her mind. 她心里还暗暗地有点不放心。', '名词复数: anxieties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('credit', '[\'kredɪt]', 'n.信用；荣誉；学分；赞扬；贷款；赊欠；贷方；存款 (复)credits: 演职员名单. v.归功于；相信；记入贷方', '1. Credit counseling helped us get out from under. 信用咨询使我们免除了忧虑 2. Where can I see my credit score? 我在哪能看到我的信用分数? 3. They are working hard for the credit of China. 他们在为中国的荣誉而努力工作。 4. You must pass the examination to get credit for the course. 你必须通过考试才能获得那门课程的学分。 5. At the time, we used to credit everything to one person. 那时大家把什么都归功于一个人。', '过去式: credited 过去分词: credited 现在分词: crediting 第三人称单数: credits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hear', '[hɪr]', 'v.得知；倾听；听到；听证', '1. How did you hear about us? How did you hear about this job? 你是如何得知我们的?如何得知这个工作的? 2. Have you heard the news? 你听到那消息了吗？ 3. I heard (that) he was ill. 我听说他病了。 4. We\'d better hear what they have to say. 我们还是听听他们要说些什么吧。', '名词: hearer 过去式: heard 过去分词: heard 现在分词: hearing 第三人称单数: hears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hijack', '[\'haɪdʒæk]', 'vt.劫持；劫机 n.劫持', '1. They planned to hijack a plane. 他们计划劫持一架飞机。 2. The plane is hijacked by six armed terrorists. 该飞机被6个武装的恐怖主义者所劫持。 3. The bandits hijacked the lorry and killed the driver 土匪劫持了卡车并杀害的司机 4. They planned to hijack a plane. 他们计划劫持一架飞机。 5. There is no sign of a let-up in the hijack crisis. 绑架危机毫无缓和迹象。', '名词: hijacker');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elderly', '[\'eldərli]', 'adj.年老的；年长的', '1. Vicious thugs attacked an elderly man. 歹徒们袭击了一个老大爷。 2. Many elderly people live an idle life. 许多老年人过着悠闲的生活。 3. I appreciate their trust in elderly men like me. 感谢大家对我们这些老头子的信任。 4. In the presence of elderly visitors our son was a model of decorum. 我们的儿子在来访的长辈面前彬彬有礼。', '名词: elderliness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('germ', '[dʒɜːrm]', 'n.细菌；微生物；胚芽', '1. Germs may invade the organism. 细菌会侵入有机体。 2. Germs are invisible to the naked eye. 细菌用肉眼看不见。 3. Disinfectant kills germs. 消毒剂灭杀细菌。 4. This is a ubiquitous germ that lives in nature and can be found in the soil or water. 这是一种在自然界普遍存在的微生物，甚至在土壤和水源中都可以存在。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tide', '[taɪd]', 'n.趋势；潮流；潮汐；潮水 v.渡过；（使）随潮漂流', '1. For a moment the tide almost turned against him. 在短短的时间内，舆论的趋势几乎变得对他不利。 2. We should be naturalized to the new tide of the world. 我们必须顺应新的世界潮流。 3. It once again proves that no one can stem the tide of history. 这再一次地证明，历史的潮流是谁也阻挡不住的。 4. The attraction of the moon for the earth causes the tide. 月亮对地球的引力引起潮汐。 5. The loan is enough to tide them over the difficulties. 这笔贷款足以使他们渡过难关。', '过去式: tided 过去分词: tided 现在分词: tiding 第三人称单数: tides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ear', '[ɪr]', 'n.听觉；耳朵；倾听 n.麦穗 vi.抽穗', '1. She plays the piano entirely by ear. 他演奏钢琴完全凭听觉记忆,不用乐谱。 2. If this news ever reaches her ears, she\'ll be furious. 这个消息万一传到她的耳朵里，她一定得大发雷霆。 3. He gave the boy\'s ear a painful tweak. 他用力拧了一下那男孩的耳朵。 4. The dog\'s ear pricked up at the sound. 狗听到声音后竖起了耳朵。 5. Some people like eating the ear of wheat. 有些人喜欢吃麦穗。 6. The corn will soon ear. 玉米不久就要结穗了。', '形容词: earless 过去式: eared 过去分词: eared 现在分词: earing 第三人称单数: ears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intimidate', '[ɪn\'tɪmɪdeɪt]', 'vt.胁迫；威胁；恐吓', '1. Nobody was going to intimidate them. 没有人能胁迫他们。 2. He was intimidated into silence. 他吓得不敢作声。 3. Bob intimidate the witness into silence. 鲍勃威胁证人保持沉默。 4. Your sons don\'t intimidate me. And neither do you. 你的儿子们威胁不了我,你也一样。', '副词: intimidatingly 名词: intimidation 过去式: intimidated 过去分词: intimidated 现在分词: intimidating 第三人称单数: intimidates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('book', '[bʊk]', 'n.书；本子 v.预订；记录在案', '1. That student lost his book yesterday. 那个学生昨天丢了书。 2. Write the essay in your (exercise-)books, not on rough paper. 把文章写在练习簿里，不要写在草稿纸上。 3. I\'ll book you on a direct flight to London. 我将为你预订直飞伦敦的航班。 4. You\'ll have to book early if you want to see that fashion show. 你要想看那场时装表演的话，就得早点儿定座位。', '名词: booker 过去式: booked 过去分词: booked 现在分词: booking 第三人称单数: books');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('duty', '[\'duːti]', 'n.义务；职责；责任；税；关税', '1. I feel it my duty to speak frankly to you. 我觉得我有义务要坦白地对你说。 2. She was ashamed to admit that she hadn\'t done her duty. 她羞愧地承认她没有尽到自己的义务。 3. He is on night duty three days a week. 他一个星期要上三天夜班。 4. He was dismissed for his neglect of duty. 他因玩忽职守而被开除了。', '名词复数: duties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('puzzle', '[\'pʌzl]', 'n.难题；谜；迷惑；拼图游戏 vt.使为难；使困惑 vi.苦思；迷惑', '1. Will you help me to solve this puzzle? 你能帮助我解决这个难题吗? 2. He sat frowning over a crossword puzzle. 他坐着皱着眉头在思考纵横字谜。 3. Her decision was a puzzle to him. 她的决定对他来说是个谜。 4. She could not get the puzzle out of her mind. 她无法解开心中的疑虑。 5. The question puzzled me. 这个问题把我难住了。 6. I saw him puzzle over a math problem. 我看见他正在苦心思索一道数学题。', '名词: puzzler 过去式: puzzled 过去分词: puzzled 现在分词: puzzling 第三人称单数: puzzles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('funeral', '[\'fjuːnərəl]', 'adj.葬礼(的) n.葬礼', '1. Funeral customs vary with different religions. 葬仪的习俗因宗教不同而不同。 2. The bishop conducted her funeral service. 主教引导了她的葬礼仪式。 3. He asked for no funeral oration. 他不要人在葬礼上宣读悼词。 4. Their cars headed the funeral procession. 他们的车队在葬礼队伍的最前面。 5. A funeral is a somber occasion. 葬礼是个忧郁的场合。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('journey', '[\'dʒɜːrni]', 'n.旅程；旅行；行程 v.旅行', '1. It was a long journey, but we eventually arrived. 旅程很长，但我们最后还是到达了。 2. He told a very descriptive account of his journey. 他对旅行作了十分生动的叙述。 3. He is going to make a long journey. 他要作一次长途旅行。 4. Let him continue on his journey. 让他继续他的行程吧。 5. They will journey across the continent in less than four hours. 不到四个小时，他们就穿越了这个大陆。', '名词: journeyer 名词复数: journeys 过去式: journeyed 过去分词: journeyed 现在分词: journeying 第三人称单数: journeys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prince', '[prɪns]', 'n.王子；亲王；诸侯', '1. The magician metamorphosed the frog into a prince. 魔术师把青蛙变成了王子。 2. The prince remained loyal throughout. 王子自始至终忠贞不渝。 3. Prince Charles was invested as Prince of Wales in 1969. 查尔斯王子於1969年受封为威尔士亲王。 4. His Highness Prince Charles will attend the meeting. 查尔斯亲王殿下将出席本次会议。', '名词: princeship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('augment', '[ɔːɡ\'ment]', 'vt.增加 n.增加；补充物', '1. They hit upon another idea to augment their income. 他们又想出一个增加收入的办法。 2. Hotel workers depend on tips to augment their usually small salaries. 饭店的工作人员主要靠小费来增加他平时微薄的收入。 3. He augments his income by teaching in the evenings. 他晚上去教书以增加收入。 4. They hit upon another idea to augment their income. 他们又想出一个增加收入的办法。', '形容词: augmentable 名词: augmenter 过去式: augmented 过去分词: augmented 现在分词: augmenting 第三人称单数: augments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stubborn', '[\'stʌbərn]', 'adj.顽固的；倔强的；难对付的', '1. That stubborn man always cleaves to his idea. 那固执的人不愿改变想法。 2. The child has a stubborn temper. 这个小孩脾气执拗。 3. This detergent can remove stubborn stains. 这种去污剂能去除难洗的污渍。 4. I have a stubborn cold and cough day and night. 我得了很难治的感冒，日夜咳嗽。', '副词: stubbornly 比较级: stubborner 最高级: stubbornest 名词: stubbornness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('area', '[\'eriə]', 'n.面积；地区，地段；区域；领域', '1. The farm has an area of 100 square kilometers. 这个农场占地100平方公里。 2. The area of the office is 35 square meters. 办公室的面积是35平方米。 3. This area has not been covered by the communication net. 这个地区还不在通讯网的覆盖之内。 4. We are going to build a school in this area. 我们准备在这个区域内建一所学校。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tax', '[tæks]', 'n.税；负担 v.斥责；课税；使 ... 负重荷', '1. She was fined for tax evasion. 她因逃税而被罚款。 2. Her accountant was good at exploiting tax loopholes. 她的会计善于利用税收漏洞。 3. The care of six children is a tax on her energy. 照料六个孩子成了她精力上很大的负担。 4. Climbing stairs is a tax on a weak heart. 爬楼梯对于心脏功能不强的人来说是一个沉重的负担。 5. He was taxed with neglecting the safety regulations. 他由于忽视安全操作规程而受到责备。', '名词: taxer 过去式: taxed 过去分词: taxed 现在分词: taxing 第三人称单数: taxes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cube', '[kjuːb]', 'n.立方体；立方 vt.求 ... 的立方 adj.立方的', '1. A cube is a three-dimensional object. 立方体是三维物体。 2. Three cubed is twenty-seven. 三的立方是二十七。 3. If you cube 1 0 , the result is 1 0 0 0 . 如果你求10的立方，得出的结果是1000。 4. The National Aquatic Center is also called \"water cube \". 国家游泳中心又被称为“水立方”。', '名词: cuber 过去式: cubed 过去分词: cubed 现在分词: cubing 第三人称单数: cubes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recruit', '[rɪ\'kruːt]', 'v.吸收(新成员)；征兵；招聘 n.新成员；新兵', '1. We are having difficulties in recruiting well-qualified staff. 我们难以招募到素质好的职员。 2. His job was to recruit for the army. 他的工作是为陆军募兵。 3. We lower the standards in order to recruit real talents. 我们降低标准是为了招纳真正的人才。 4. This job presents many difficulties to the new recruit. 这件工作对那个新手来说困难重重。', '名词: recruiter 过去式: recruited 过去分词: recruited 现在分词: recruiting 第三人称单数: recruits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chemistry', '[\'kemɪstri]', 'n.化学', '1. I prefer chemistry to physics. 我喜欢化学甚于物理。 2. We have three periods of chemistry a week. 我们一星期三节化学课。 3. No one can cope with him in Chemistry. 在化学方面，谁也比不上他。 4. We will do a Chemistry experiment this Friday. 这个周五我们要做化学试验。', '名词复数: chemistries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wing', '[wɪŋ]', 'n.翅膀；翼 v.飞过；空运；临时发挥', '1. The hen tucked her head under her wing. 那母鸡把头缩在翅膀下。 2. A seagull fluttered down with an injured wing. 一只海鸥拍打着翅膀飞落下来。 3. The bird\'s left wing was hurt. 这只鸟的左翼受伤了。 4. Wild gooses wing regularly,haste and idle. 大雁整齐地飞过', '过去式: winged 过去分词: winged 现在分词: winging 第三人称单数: wings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discovery', '[dɪ\'skʌvəri]', 'n.发现；发现物', '1. The new discovery caused a great sensation. 这项新发现很轰动。 2. New scientific discoveries are being made everyday. 每天都有新的科学发现。 3. A collector of rare insects will show us some of his latest discoveries. 一位稀有昆虫采集家将给我们看一些他的最新发现。 4. Like many discoveries, atomic power can be used for good or evil. 正如人类发现的许多事物一样，原子能既可用来为善，也可用以作恶。', '名词复数: discoveries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('review', '[rɪ\'vjuː]', 'n.复习；回顾；检讨；评审 vt.检阅；评论；温习；检讨 vi.写评论', '1. Before the examination we have a review of the term\'s work. 考试之前，我们复习一学期的功课。 2. A succinct review of this problem with an excellent bibliography has recently appeared. 关于这个问题的一个简明的复习和一份极好的文献目录最近已发表。 3. Perhaps we need a quick review of what we\'ve gone through so far. 或许我们应很快地回顾一下我们前一段时间的工作。 4. Implementation of this phase is under review subject to the finalisation of the statutory plan. 当局现正检讨这期工程的实施，检讨结果视乎拟定法定图则的工作而定。 5. On the square, the commander reviewed the powerful and grandiose guard of honor. 首长在广场上检阅了威武雄壮的仪仗队。 6. Sometimes he reviewed for the principal papers. 他有时为各大报写些评论文章。', '形容词: reviewable 过去式: reviewed 过去分词: reviewed 现在分词: reviewing 第三人称单数: reviews');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prospective', '[prə\'spektɪv]', 'adj.预期的；未来的', '1. We receive prospective results in the experiment. 我们在实验中得到了预期的结果。 2. Tom is the prospective buyer of my house. 汤姆是可能购买我的房屋的人。 3. I hope you can give this your immediate attention so that I can notify the prospective guests promptly. 我希望您能对此予以迅速考虑，以便我能及时通知期待的客人。 4. She is married to a prospective lawyer. 她嫁给了一个未来的律师。', '副词: prospectively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('state', '[steɪt]', 'n.情形；状态；国家；州；政府 adj.国家的；州的；国事礼仪的 v.陈述；声明；说明；规定', '1. She wept to see him in such a state. 她一见他那种情形簌簌泪下。 2. The house has fallen into a state of neglect. 这所房屋已处于荒废的状态。 3. The head of state was deposed by the army. 国家元首被军队废黜了。 4. Alaska is a state of ample size. 阿拉斯加是个大州。 5. He was wary of telling state secrets. 他小心翼翼以免泄漏国家机密。 6. Please state the facts honestly. 请如实地陈述事实。', '过去式: stated 过去分词: stated 现在分词: stating 第三人称单数: states');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('win', '[wɪn]', 'v.赢；赢得；获胜；获得 n.胜利', '1. That horse is a cinch to win the next race. 那匹马在下一场比赛中肯定赢。 2. She has a fervent desire to win. 她有著强烈的获胜欲望。 3. She needs to win this point to level the score. 她要赢得这一分才能将比分扳平。 4. He is expected to win the game with ease. 预计他在比赛中会轻易获胜。 5. The team has chalked up its fifth win in a row. 这队一连五次取得胜利。', '过去式: won 过去分词: won 现在分词: winning 第三人称单数: wins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wholesome', '[\'hoʊlsəm]', 'adj.有益健康的；合乎卫生的', '1. Bread and milk is wholesome breakfast. 面包和牛奶加有益于健康的早餐。 2. You should read some wholesome books. 你应当读些有益的书。 3. It is not wholesome to eat without washing your hands. 不洗手吃饭是不卫生的。', '副词: wholesomely 比较级: wholesomer 最高级: wholesomest 名词: wholesomeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reception', '[rɪ\'sepʃn]', 'n.接待；反应；接待处；欢迎；接收；招待会', '1. The bridal suite was prepared for the reception of the honeymooners. 新婚套间已准备好以接待度蜜月的人。 2. The play got a favourable reception from the critics. 该剧获评论界好评。 3. Wait for me at reception. 在接待处等我吧。 4. The bridal suite was prepared for the reception of the honeymooners. 新婚套间已准备好以接待度蜜月的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('FALSE', '[fɔːls]', 'adj.假的；人造的；不真实的；错误的；虚伪的 adv.欺骗地', '1. The impostor traveled on a false passport. 那个伪装者用一本假护照旅行。 2. Lucy had a pair of false eyelashes today. 露西今天戴了一副假睫毛。 3. They lulled me into a false sense of security. 他们哄骗我，让我产生了一种虚假的安全感。 4. After several false starts, she became a successful journalist. 她开始时遇到几次挫折,后来成为能干的记者 5. He is just playing me false, which never surprises me. 他只是在欺骗我,那一点我从来不感到奇怪。', '副词: falsely 比较级: falser 最高级: falsest 名词: falseness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('architect', '[\'ɑːrkɪtekt]', 'n.建筑师 n.【喻】缔造者；创造者', '1. He is known as a successful architect. 他以成功的建筑师闻名。 2. The author of the guidebook is an architect by profession. 该旅行指南的作者任职建筑师。 3. The architect was given/presented with a blank cheque to design a new city centre. 设计师被授予全权设计一个新的城市中心区。 4. He was one of the architects of the republic. 他是这个共和国的缔造者之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mist', '[mɪst]', 'n.雾；迷蒙；朦胧不清 vt.使…模糊；蒙上雾 vi.使模糊；下雾', '1. A mist of perfume hung in the air. 空气中飘溢著香水的雾气。 2. Everything was covered in mist. 一切都笼罩在雾霭中。 3. She could hardly recognize her son through the mist of tears that filled her eyes. 她泪眼蒙蒙，几乎不能认出自己的儿子。 4. I turn from my work and my eyes fill with the mist. 我劳作回来眼神朦胧不清。 5. Our breath is misting up the car windows. 我们呼出的气渐渐给汽车的窗户上蒙上一层水蒸气。 6. But when he wakes, hours later, the dream has turned to mist. 但是当他醒来之后,过了几个钟头,这些梦就变成了一团迷雾。', '过去式: misted 过去分词: misted 现在分词: misting 第三人称单数: mists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brand', '[brænd]', 'n.烙印；商标；牌子；标记 vt.加污名于；铭记；打烙印', '1. As an author who was in a period when the new and the old interlaced, Cervantes had a brand of two ages inevitably. 作为新旧两个时代交替期的作家,塞万提斯身上不可避免地带有两个时代的烙印。 2. You may personalize the design to match your company\'s existing brand identity and design specifications. 您也可以进行个性化设计,使其符合公司的现有商标与设计规范。 3. The advertising manager may set as a goal for advertising an increase of 15 percent in consumer brand awareness in the next six months. 广告经理确定的目标为:在今后的6个月里，通过广告，提高消费者商标知晓率的15%25。 4. She\'s gone over to a milder brand of cigarettes. 她已改吸另一牌子味道较淡的香烟。 5. Those who have triumphantly withstood such strains may brand his name. 那些成功地经受了严峻考验的人们或许会污辱他的名声。', '名词: brander 过去式: branded 过去分词: branded 现在分词: branding 第三人称单数: brands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('category', '[\'kætəɡɔːri]', 'n.种类；类别；范畴', '1. There are different categories of books in a library. 图书馆里有各种不同种类的书籍。 2. They fall into different categories. 他们属于不同的类别。 3. They misplaced this book under another category. 他们把它错放到另一个类别去了。 4. How can a scientific category have its derivatives? 科学范畴何以能衍生?', '名词复数: categories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('corrupt', '[kə\'rʌpt]', 'adj.腐败的；堕落的；讹误的 vt.贿赂；使恶化；使腐烂 vi.腐败；腐烂', '1. She wrote a book declaiming against our corrupt society. 她写了一本书抨击我们这腐败的社会。 2. The corrupt judge dismissed the case without a hearing. 腐败的法官没有听审就驳回了这个案子。 3. The official led a corrupt life. 这个官员过着堕落的生活。 4. The manuscript is so corrupt that parts of it make no sense at all. 这稿子由于讹误太多，以致有的部分意义不明。 5. He was sent to prison for trying to corrupt a policeman with money. 他因为试图用钱贿赂一名警察而被送入监狱。 6. Complete power corrupts completely. 绝对的权力造成绝对的腐败。', '形容词: corruptive 副词: corruptly 名词: corrupter 过去式: corrupted 过去分词: corrupted 现在分词: corrupting 第三人称单数: corrupts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kettle', '[\'ketl]', 'n.水壶；坑穴', '1. The kettle is boiling. 壶里的水开了。 2. The switch on the kettle won\'t stay down. 这个水壶上的开关按下时卡不住了。 3. This kettle whistles when it boils. 这水壶在水开时会哔哔作响。 4. Kettle can also form as the result of floods caused by the sudden drainage of an ice-dammed lake. 因为冰堰湖的突然泄流造成的洪水也有可能形成锅穴。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kiss', '[kɪs]', 'n.吻；轻触 v.吻；轻触', '1. Look like he\'s going to haul off and kiss the girl. 看上去他会突然吻那个姑娘一下。 2. How do you steal a kiss from a girl like that? 你怎么赢得像那样了不起的女孩的吻的？ 3. How do you steal a kiss from a girl like that? 你怎么赢得像那样了不起的女孩的吻的？ 4. He gave her a kiss that betokened his affection. 他给她一个表示爱的吻。', '形容词: kissable 过去式: kissed 过去分词: kissed 现在分词: kissing 第三人称单数: kisses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('print', '[prɪnt]', 'v.印刷；出版；打印；铭刻 n.印刷字体；版画；印刷；印记；印刷物；印花 adj.印刷的', '1. How many copies shall we print from the negative? 用这张底片我们要印多少张相片? 2. His second book is already in print. 他的第二本书已出版。 3. He founded his own press to print them. 他自己成立印刷厂出版这些书。 4. This printer can print 40 pages in a minute. 这台打印机一分钟能打印40页。 5. The print is too small for me to read without glasses. 印刷字体太小，我不带眼镜就看不清。 6. Headlines are written in large print. 标题是用大号字体印刷的。', '过去式: printed 过去分词: printed 现在分词: printing 第三人称单数: prints');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aspire', '[ə\'spaɪər]', 'v.热望；立志', '1. Do you aspire to know the heights, and depths, and lengths, and breadths? 你是否热望要知道上帝的长阔高深？ 2. And thousands of young players aspire to be like him. 千千万万的年轻球手立志要想成为象他那样的英雄。 3. Woman should not only aspire to be educated but also persue independence. 女性不仅应该立志接受教育，还应该追求独立。', '副词: aspiringly 名词: aspirer 过去式: aspired 过去分词: aspired 现在分词: aspiring 第三人称单数: aspires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cardinal', '[\'kɑːrdɪnl]', 'n.红衣主教；鲜红色；基数；北美红雀 adj.主要的；深红色的', '1. I\'ve had dinner with Bill and Cardinal Spellman. 我同比尔和斯佩尔曼红衣主教一起吃过晚饭。 2. The cardinal includes 1, 2, 3, etc. 基数词包括1、2、3等等。 3. A cardinal perched momently on the dogwood branch. 一只北美红雀在山茱萸上停留了片刻。 4. Every one suspects himself of at least one of the cardinal virtues. 每个人都认为他自己至少有一种主要的品德。', '名词: cardinalship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('privilege', '[\'prɪvəlɪdʒ]', 'n.特权；荣幸；特别恩典；基本人权 vt.给特权；免除', '1. I had the privilege of meeting the queen. 我有会见王后的特权。 2. It is a great privilege to know you. 认识你是一件难得的事。 3. It was a privilege to work with him. 和他在一起工作是一项殊荣。 4. Kings cannot privilege what God forbade. 国王不能原谅上帝不允许做的事。', '过去式: privileged 过去分词: privileged 现在分词: privileging 第三人称单数: privileges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('document', '[\'dɑːkjumənt]', 'n.文件；公文；文档 vt.记载；(用文件等)证明', '1. She signed her name to the document. 她在文件上签了名。 2. He persuaded her to sign the document by guile. 他用欺骗手段说服她在文件上签字。 3. The official document was misworded. 这公文的措词不当。 4. A document issued to sub-branches shall be sealed by all the issuers. 联合下发的公文，发文机关都应当加盖印章。 5. The history of this area is very well documented. 这个地区的历史档案保存得很好。', '形容词: documental 名词: documenter 过去式: documented 过去分词: documented 现在分词: documenting 第三人称单数: documents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('likewise', '[\'laɪkwaɪz]', 'adv.同样地；此外；（表示感觉相同）我也是', '1. Watch him and do likewise. 注意看着他然后照样做。 2. I told him to watch me and do likewise. 我叫他仔细看著我,并且照样做。 3. She sprinkled her with the juices of aconite, and immediately her hair came off, and her nose and ears likewise. 她用附子汁向阿拉喀涅洒去，她的头发马上就脱光了，她的鼻子和耳朵也掉了。 4. They went on foot and I did likewise. 他们步行去,我也步行去了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shipment', '[\'ʃɪpmənt]', 'n.装运；货物；装船；出货', '1. Better to postpone the shipment than to cancel the contract. 与其撤约还不如延期装运。 2. We have reached an agreement with him in regard to the shipment. 我们已经就装运问题同他达成协议。 3. A signed invoice presumes receipt of the shipment. 经过签字的发票表示货物已经收到。 4. The merchant had received a shipment of tea. 这个商人收到了一船茶叶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('notable', '[\'noʊtəbl]', 'adj.显著的；著名的 n.名人', '1. The difference contrast is notable. 差别对比是显著的。 2. This book had a notable impact on literature and art. 这本书对文学艺术产生显著的影响。 3. Tsim Sha Tsui is a notable tourist destination. 尖沙咀是著名的游客区。 4. You can also take in some of the notable architectural monuments. 你也可以将一些著名的纪念性建筑包括在参观的项目中。 5. He is the most notable son of Manchester. 他是曼切斯特最显赫的名人。', '副词: notably 名词: notableness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('radiant', '[\'reɪdiənt]', 'adj.发光的；明亮的；辐射的', '1. As you evolve, the petals unfold to reveal a radiant jewel in the center. 当你进化的时候，花瓣绽开显现出中心发光的珠宝。 2. Giant, snow-white in colour and gleaming bright, will beget a radiant people. 一位巨人，雪白的肤色，闪烁着明亮的光，会产生发光的人。 3. Giant, snow-white in colour and gleaming bright, will beget a radiant people. 一位巨人，雪白的肤色，闪烁着明亮的光，会产生发光的人。 4. Quantum theory proposes that radiant energy is transmitted in discrete units. 量子理论的提出辐射的能量能传递离散的单位。', '副词: radiantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('porch', '[pɔːrtʃ]', 'n.门廊', '1. A pigeon perched on our porch railing. 一只鸽子栖息在我们门廊的栏杆上。 2. I met that person at the porch of the church. 我是在教堂的门廊处遇到那个人的。 3. The roof inclines over the porch . 这个屋顶朝那门廊上面倾斜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('installment', '[ɪn\'stɔːlmənt]', 'n.分期付款；部分；分册 n.安装；安置', '1. We will pay for houses by monthly installments. 我们将按月分期付款买房。 2. Buy goods on the installment plan has become epidemic in recent year. 近几年来，用分期付款的办法购物十分流行。 3. The last installment will be split into two movies. 故事的最后一部分将会拍成两部电影。 4. The installment of the new system took an hour. 安装新系统花了一个小时。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contain', '[kən\'teɪn]', 'vt.容纳；包含；抑制；克制 vi.自制', '1. The atlas contains forty maps. 这个地图集有四十幅地图。 2. Does each cup contain the same amount of milk? 每个杯子里的牛奶都一样多吗? 3. This book contains all the information you need. 这本书包含你所需的一切资料。 4. I could hardly contain my curiosity. 我简直无法克制我的好奇心 5. She couldn\'t contain herself for joy. 她高兴地难以自制。', '形容词: containable 过去式: contained 过去分词: contained 现在分词: containing 第三人称单数: contains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shield', '[ʃiːld]', 'n.盾；盾状物；防卫物 vt.保护；庇护', '1. The shield protected him from the blows of his enemy. 这盾牌保护他免受敌人的打击。 2. There is a shield in the badge of PLA men. 解放军的徽章上有着盾状物。 3. He must pile more sand on top as a shield. 他必须在顶上多加些沙土作为防御物。 4. Motorcyclists must wear helmets to shield them from injury. 摩托车手必须戴头盔保护自己免受伤害。', '名词: shielder 过去式: shielded 过去分词: shielded 现在分词: shielding 第三人称单数: shields');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('handbook', '[\'hændbʊk]', 'n.手册；指南', '1. This medical handbook helps a lot. 这本医药手册很有用。 2. She is reading a handbook on gardening. 她正在阅读一本园艺手册。 3. I bought a handbook of English grammar last week. 上星期我买了一本英文文法手册。 4. Could you get a handbook of London for me? 你能为我买一本伦敦旅游指南吗?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('owner', '[\'oʊnər]', 'n.所有人；物主', '1. The property revert to its original owner in1998. 财产于1998年将归还原所有人。 2. She is not the true owner of this house. 她不是这所房子的真正所有人。 3. The stolen property must be restored to its owner. 赃物必须物归原主。 4. I am the rightful owner of this car. 我是这辆新车的合法主人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('defect', '[\'diːfekt]', 'n.缺点；缺陷 vi.背叛', '1. If it were not for this defect, I shall hire him at once. 如果不是因为这个缺点，我会马上雇用他。 2. The new car had to be withdrawn from the market because of a mechanical defect. 那种新汽车因有机械缺陷只好撤出市场。 3. We thought that his troops might defect. 我们认为他的部队会叛变。', '名词: defection 过去式: defected 过去分词: defected 现在分词: defecting 第三人称单数: defects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('indignant', '[ɪn\'dɪɡnənt]', 'adj.愤慨的；愤愤不平的', '1. People are indignant by their shooting of innocent civilians. 对于他们枪杀无辜平民，人们感到义愤填膺。 2. He is indignant at the false accusation. 他对被诬告愤愤不平。', '副词: indignantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('delivery', '[dɪ\'lɪvəri]', 'n.传递；交付；递送；分娩；转让；演讲姿态；投球', '1. You have to pay a premium for express delivery. 你得支付特快投递的补加费用。 2. If you can guarantee punctual delivery, we shall place order with you. 如果你能保证按时交付，我们将给你定购。 3. Please send this parcel by express delivery. 请用快递寄送这个包裹。 4. The snowstorm delayed the delivery of the mail. 那场暴风雪延误了邮件的递送。', '名词复数: deliveries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expression', '[ɪk\'spreʃn]', 'n.表情；表示；表达；词句；措辞；表现；挤压', '1. He always shows a doleful expression. 他总是露出忧郁的表情。 2. She gave expression to her sadness. 她流露出了悲伤之情。 3. The scenery was beautiful beyond expression. 那风景美丽得无法形容。 4. I haven\'t heard that expression before. 我以前从未听到过这个词语。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chair', '[tʃer]', 'n.椅子；(会议的)主席 vt.主持；当 ... 的主席', '1. Her hands rested on the arms of her chair. 她的双手搁在椅子的扶手上。 2. He sat in a chair near the door. 他坐在靠门的一把椅子上。 3. Mr Smith will take the chair at the next meeting. 下次会议将由史密斯先生主持。 4. He was elected chair of the city council. 他当选为市议会主席。 5. I\'d like you to chair the meeting. 我想请你主持会议。', '过去式: chaired 过去分词: chaired 现在分词: chairing 第三人称单数: chairs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bank', '[bæŋk]', 'n.银行；岸；筹码；库；田埂；堤；积云；一系列；一组；一排；一团；用于循环再利用的废旧物品回收站 v.把钱存入银行；开户；筑堤防护；堆积', '1. He has a large deposit in the bank. 他在银行有大笔存款。 2. The town stands on the left bank of the river. 城镇位于河的左岸。 3. They walked along the fields bank，chatting happily. 他们沿着田埂,开心地边走边聊。 4. The bank burst and totally collapsed. 整个堤坝全体溃决。 5. They like to bank with the Royal Bank. 他们喜欢把钱存在皇家银行。', '过去式: banked 过去分词: banked 现在分词: banking 第三人称单数: banks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('manner', '[\'mænər]', 'n.举止；礼貌；方式；习俗', '1. He is easy in conversation and graceful in manner. 他谈吐从容,举止优雅。 2. There is a noticeable coolness in his manner. 在他的举止中表现出一种明显的冷淡。 3. It is bad manners to interrupt. 打断别人说话是不礼貌的。 4. He often speaks in the most understated manner possible. 他说话尽可能保持低调。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commonplace', '[\'kɑːmənpleɪs]', 'adj.平凡的；陈腐的 n.常事；老生常谈；普通的东西', '1. Poets interpret the commonplace freshly. 诗人能把平凡的事物描绘得有声有色。 2. He was an unambitious man destined for a commonplace job. 他是一个没有野心的人，注定要找一个平凡的工作。 3. Soon it will be commonplace for men to travel to the moon. 人们去月球旅行很快就会成为常事。 4. What he has said is a mere commonplace. 他所说的无非是老生常谈而已。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pine', '[paɪn]', 'n.松树；松木 vi.消瘦；渴望', '1. The pine trees defy severe cold. 松树不畏严寒。 2. It\'s a noted place for its pine tree and springs. 这是一个以松树和泉水著称的地方。 3. There is a pine forest near our house. 我们家附近有片松树林。 4. Pine is a soft wood and teak is a hard wood. 松木是软木，柚木是硬木。 5. He pined away after his daughter died. 他的女儿死后，他逐渐变得憔悴了。', '过去式: pined 过去分词: pined 现在分词: pining 第三人称单数: pines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('breakfast', '[\'brekfəst]', 'n.早餐 v.吃早餐；用早餐', '1. We were having breakfast. 我们正在吃早餐。 2. He seldom eats breakfast. 他很少吃早餐。 3. She juiced an orange for her breakfast. 她用一只橙子榨汁作早餐饮料。 4. Mr. Smith left for London after breakfast. 史密斯先生吃过早餐后就动身去伦敦了。 5. We breakfasted early. 我们很早吃早餐。', '名词: breakfaster 过去式: breakfasted 过去分词: breakfasted 现在分词: breakfasting 第三人称单数: breakfasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eagle', '[\'iːɡl]', 'n.鹰', '1. The eagle held a mouse in its claws. 鹰用爪抓住了老鼠。 2. The eagle dived down on the rabbit. 那只鹰向兔子猛扑下来。 3. The eagle poised in mid-air ready to swoop on its prey. 那鹰在半空中盘旋准备扑向猎物。', '过去式: eagled 过去分词: eagled 现在分词: eagling 第三人称单数: eagles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surroundings', '[sə\'raʊndɪŋz]', 'n.周围的事物；环境 名词surrounding的复数形式.', '1. I was oblivious of my surroundings. 我没有注意到周围的事物。 2. Happiness comes from within your heart, not from your surroundings. 幸福来自于你的内心世界，而不是你周围的事物。 3. We are living in pleasant surroundings. 我们生活在舒适的环境中。 4. He immediately noticed the amenity of his new surroundings. 他立刻觉察到了新环境的宜人之处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('draw', '[drɔː]', 'v.拖；接近；画；提取；拉；绘制 n.平局；抽签；拉；拽；吸引人的事物', '1. The horses draw the wagon. 马拖货车。 2. Our car broke down and we had to draw it to a garage. 我们的车坏了, 不得不把它拖到修车厂去。 3. The season was drawing to its dusty end. 喧嚣纷扰的社交季节逐渐接近尾声。 4. Mary drew a house on the paper. 玛丽在纸上画了一栋房子。 5. They had been dueling for hours and finally called a draw. 他们一直决斗了数小时，最后打成平局。', '过去式: drew 过去分词: drawn 现在分词: drawing 第三人称单数: draws');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('digital', '[\'dɪdʒɪtl]', 'adj.数字的；数码的；手指的；计数的', '1. Most of the computers we are using are digital computers. 我们正在使用的计算机大多数是数字计算机。 2. This is my newly bought digital watch. 这是我新买的数字手表。 3. I just looked at the digital map. 我刚查看完数字地图。 4. Digital cameras can eat up a lot of power. 数码相机是很费电的。', '副词: digitally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pickup', '[\'pɪkʌp]', 'n.拾起；（开车)去接；搭便车者；获得；加速；拾音器；小型卡车；实况转播；（生意）好转；<美俚>逮捕；发现，截获；固定器；随便买的东西 adj.临时的；凑合的', '1. About six weeks after he was paroled, he was drinking beer with a friend in the other man\'s pickup truck, with a gun rack in the back. 获得假释大约六个星期之后，他和一个朋友在对方的敞蓬货车里喝啤酒，车后部有一个枪架。 2. We reach the outskirts of town and begin to pickup speed. 我们到达市郊後开始加速。 3. Assuming Measurement by Accelerometer or Velocity Pickup securely mounted as Close as Possible to Bearing Housing. 假定加速计或速度传感器安装在离轴承座尽可能近的地方采集数据。 4. Once a pickup in orders becomes evident, the stage is set for the expansion phase. 一旦订货出现明显好转，就开始了扩张阶段。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('physical', '[\'fɪzɪkl]', 'adj.物质的；身体的；体力的；物理的；肉体上的，身体上的 <美>体格检查', '1. It\'s a physical impossibility to be in two places at one time. 同时在两地是自然规律上不可能的事。 2. Physical disability causes mental anguish. 生理伤残会引起心理苦闷。 3. Staying up late makes him at his worst in terms of physical situation. 熬夜使得他的体力状况处于低潮。 4. For them, getting rid of heavy physical labour is a big thing 对他们来说, 摆脱重体力劳动是一件大事。', '副词: physically 名词: physicality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('during', '[\'dʊrɪŋ]', 'prep.在 ... 期间', '1. He swims every day during the summer. 他夏天每天游泳。 2. The thief broke into the house during the night. 小偷在夜间破门进入住宅。 3. He was born in China during World War II and educated in England. 他在二次大战期间生于中国,后来在英国受。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('toward', '[tə\'wɔːd]', 'prep.向；朝；对于；接近；关于；将近 adj.有希望的；有利的；逼近的', '1. He ran for dear life toward his house. 他拼命地向他的房子跑去。 2. The bus follows the road toward Beijing. 那公共汽车是顺着朝北京去的道路行驶。 3. I have shown enough forbearance toward him. 我已经对他很有耐心了。 4. The Policeman continues to shuffle toward her. 警察还是慢慢地移步接近她。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rack', '[ræk]', 'n.行李架；（放衣物、碗碟等的）架子；拷问台；折磨；（比赛开始前固定球位置的）三角框 vt.使痛苦；把...放在架子上；累计取得', '1. He put his bag on the luggage rack. 他把包放在行李架上。 2. He put his shoes on the rack. 他把鞋放在架子上。 3. The famous ancient Chinese politician ShangYang was put on the rack. 中国古代著名的政治家商鞅被施以拉肢之刑。 4. We will all be on the rack until the exam results are published. 在考试结果公布之前,我们将一直焦虑不安。 5. I was racked with doubt and pain. 我满腹疑虑,痛苦万分。', '名词: racker 过去式: racked 过去分词: racked 现在分词: racking 第三人称单数: racks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('massacre', '[\'mæsəkər]', 'n.大屠杀；<口>惨败 v.大屠杀；<口>彻底击败', '1. The massacre was a crime against humanity. 这场大屠杀是一桩反人类的罪行。 2. The press has reported the massacre of thousands of people for their religious beliefs. 新闻界报道了那场因宗教信仰原因而对千万人的大屠杀。 3. The game was a complete massacre; we lost 10-0. 那次比赛真是一次惨败，我们0比10输了。 4. Vichy government was the accessory of Nazi to massacre the Jews who lived in France. 维希政府是德国纳粹残害住在法国的犹太人的帮凶之一。', '名词: massacrer 过去式: massacred 过去分词: massacred 现在分词: massacring 第三人称单数: massacres');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alien', '[\'eɪliən]', 'n.外侨；外国人；外星人 adj.外国的；陌生的；相异的', '1. Immigrant workers were classed as resident aliens. 移民来的工人已归入外侨类。 2. She is declared an undesirable alien and deport. 她被宣布是不受欢迎的外国人并被驱逐出境。 3. I followed the alien to see where it was to go. 我跟着外星人看它朝哪儿去。 4. I ran into an old friend in the alien land. 我在异国他乡遇到故知。', '过去式: aliened 过去分词: aliened 现在分词: aliening 第三人称单数: aliens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ski', '[skiː]', 'v.滑雪 n.滑雪板；雪橇', '1. They often go skiing in December. 他们经常在十二月份去滑雪。 2. I am learning to ski. 我正在学滑雪。 3. The trail can be skied. 这条小道上可以滑雪。 4. The girl asked her father to buy a pair of skis for her. 那个女孩请求她的父亲给她买一副滑雪板。', '形容词: skiable 名词: skier 名词复数: skis 过去式: skied 过去分词: skied 现在分词: skiing 第三人称单数: skis');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dare', '[der]', 'vt.敢；挑战；冒...的风险 vi.勇于；胆敢 aux.胆敢 n.胆量；挑战', '1. The gymnast dared a breathtakingly difficult move. 这位体操选手敢于做惊险的高难度动作 2. He dared me to jump over the river. 他激我跳过河。 3. He dared his grandfather\'s displeasure when he left the family business. 他不顾祖父的不悦，放下了家族的生意。 4. I would do it if I dared. 如果我有勇气我就做。 5. I dare say you are right. 我认为你是对的。 6. Don\'t worry! I am just trying my dare. 不用担心！我只不过在试试自己的胆量而已。', '名词: darer 过去式: dared 过去分词: dared 现在分词: daring 第三人称单数: dares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brown', '[braʊn]', 'adj.棕色的；褐色的 n.褐色；棕色 v.（使）变褐色 Brown. n.布朗(姓氏)', '1. He had brown skin. 他的皮肤是棕色的 2. He bought a pair of dark brown shoes. 他买了一双深褐色的皮鞋。 3. Brown doesn\'t suit you. 你不适合穿褐色衣服。 4. The leaves of various shades of brown are falling down. 各种深浅不同的棕色树叶正纷纷下落。 5. Heat the butter until it browns. 把黄油加热，直到变成褐色为止。', '形容词: brownish 比较级: browner 最高级: brownest 名词: brownness 过去式: browned 过去分词: browned 现在分词: browning 第三人称单数: browns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clear', '[klɪr]', 'adj.清楚的；明确的；明白(某事)的；清晰的；清澈的；晴朗的；头脑清醒的 v.清空；清除；澄清；放晴；使明确 adv.清楚地；彻底地 n.空地', '1. I made it clear to him that I rejected his proposal. 我清楚地告诉他，我拒绝了他的建议。 2. You are a boss, as is clear from your manner. 你是一个老板,从你的举止就能很清楚地看出来。 3. There is a clear division of labor in ants. 蚂蚁间有明确的分工。 4. His height gives him a clear advantage. 他的身高使他具有明显的优势。 5. The ground should first be cleared of weeds. 这块地上的杂草应该先除干净。 6. He tried hard to speak loud and clear on that occasion. 他竭力想让自己在这种场合说话响亮清楚些。', '形容词: clearable 副词: clearly 比较级: clearer 最高级: clearest 名词: clearer 过去式: cleared 过去分词: cleared 现在分词: clearing 第三人称单数: clears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('leaf', '[liːf]', 'n.页；叶；金属薄片 v.长叶；翻页', '1. I saw him take a leaf out of the book. 我看见他从书上撕下一页。 2. The falling leaf spiralled to the ground. 落叶盘旋著飘到了地上。 3. Not a leaf nor an insect stirred. 不单是树叶，连个虫子都不动。 4. This plant has green leaves throughout the year. 这种植物终年常青。 5. The trees are just beginning to leaf. 树刚刚开始长叶子。', '名词复数: leaves 过去式: leafed 过去分词: leafed 现在分词: leafing 第三人称单数: leafs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('balance', '[\'bæləns]', 'n.平衡；天平；平静；结余；差额；调和；制衡 vt.权衡；使平衡；抵消；称重量 vi.均衡；建立平衡', '1. The girl lost her balance and fell off the balance beam. 小女孩失去了平衡，从平衡木上摔了下来。 2. Great care must be taken in the use of the balance. 这种天平使用时必须十分当心。 3. He used a very sensitive torsion balance. 他利用了一架非常灵敏的扭力天平。 4. Sunday is a great time to balance out whatever area of your life has felt disordered as of late. 星期天是你最近动荡不安的生活得到平静的大好时机。 5. You have to balance the advantages of living in a big city against the disadvantages. 你必须权衡住在大城市的利与弊。 6. The dancer could balance on one toe. 舞蹈演员可以用一个脚趾平衡。', '过去式: balanced 过去分词: balanced 现在分词: balancing 第三人称单数: balances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('knowledge', '[\'nɑːlɪdʒ]', 'n.学问；了解；知识；认识；知道', '1. He is poor in money, but rich in knowledge. 他贫于金钱， 但富于学问。 2. She has a detailed knowledge of this period. 她对这段时期的情况了解地相当详细。 3. Child as he is, he knows much knowledge of science. 尽管还是个孩子,他懂得很多科学知识。 4. They did it without my knowledge. 他们是背着我做这件事的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('faithful', '[\'feɪθfl]', 'adj.忠诚的；忠实的；忠贞的', '1. A true friend is faithful to the end. 真正的朋友到死都是忠诚的。 2. Mary is faithful to her husband. 玛丽忠实于她的丈夫。 3. His faithful pet dog bore him company. 他那忠实的爱犬给他做伴。 4. This newspaper gave a faithful account of the event. 这份报纸对那件事进行了如实的报道。', '副词: faithfully 名词: faithfulness 名词复数: faithful');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inventory', '[\'ɪnvəntɔːri]', 'n.详细目录；存货(清单) vt.编制(详细目录)', '1. The job of compiling the inventory took several hours. 编辑详细目录的工作花了好几个小时。 2. The inventory showed that the store was overstocked. 清单显示商店存货过多。 3. All of the inventory has been tagged and referenced. 所有存货清单都被贴上了标签，以备参考。 4. Is the shop inventory verified before the commencement of a sales promotion? 有否在减价开始前按公司清单核实存货? 5. He inventories the minor losses and submitted it to the management. 他将那些较小的损失编进目录，上交给管理层。', '形容词: inventorial 副词: inventorially 名词复数: inventories 过去式: inventoried 过去分词: inventoried 现在分词: inventorying 第三人称单数: inventories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('port', '[pɔːrt]', 'n.港口', '1. Rick often watched the boats returning to port in the late afternoon. 瑞克常常看到小船在傍晚回到港口。 2. The priest blessed the ship before it left port. 牧师在船离港之前为其祝福。', '过去式: ported 过去分词: ported 现在分词: porting 第三人称单数: ports');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bewilder', '[bɪ\'wɪldər]', 'vt. 使迷惑； 使 ... 不知所措', '1. You bewildered me. 你把我搞糊涂了。 2. Big city traffic bewilders me. 大城市的交通使我晕头转向。', '副词: bewilderedly 名词: bewilderedness 过去式: bewildered 过去分词: bewildered 现在分词: bewildering 第三人称单数: bewilders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('medium', '[\'miːdiəm]', 'adj.中等的；适中的 n.手段；媒介；媒体', '1. The blue cap is a medium size. 那顶蓝色的帽子就是中号的。 2. The clothes should be washed at medium temperature. 这衣服需以适中温度洗涤。 3. Commercial television is an effective medium for advertising. 商业电视是有效的广告宣传工具。 4. Sound travels through the medium of air. 声音通过空气这一媒介传播。', '名词复数: media');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ease', '[iːz]', 'n.容易；悠闲；安逸；自在 v.减轻；放松；缓和；缓慢移动', '1. He passed the test with ease. 他轻而易举地考及格了。 2. He is expected to win the game with ease. 预计他在比赛中会轻易获胜。 3. My parents are retired and now live a life of ease. 我的父母都退休了，现在过着安闲舒适的生活。 4. She is a rich woman now, and leads a life of ease. 她现在是个富婆,过着安逸的生活。 5. The pain began to ease up after she was given a sedative. 给她吃了一片镇痛药后,她的疼痛开始减轻。', '过去式: eased 过去分词: eased 现在分词: easing 第三人称单数: eases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('readily', '[\'redɪli]', 'adv.容易地；迅速地；乐意地；欣然', '1. These problems are not readily soluble. 这些问题不容易解决。 2. They can readily be brought anywhere. 它们易于携带。 3. She stood up readily. 她迅速地站了起来。 4. She readily accepted his proposal of marriage. 她乐意地接受了他的求婚。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('orderly', '[\'ɔːrdərli]', 'adj.有秩序的；整齐的；一丝不苟的 n.勤务兵；（医院的）勤务工', '1. This event disrupted the orderly process. 这个事件使有秩序的进程陷入了混乱。 2. The crowd was orderly and quiet. 人群很有秩序，也很安静。 3. Credit is an orderly market economics source. 信用是有秩序市场经济之源泉。 4. His glance ranged over the orderly rows. 他注视着一排排整齐的行列。 5. Shortly after blackout we were disturbed by an orderly making his way down the length of train with a rattle. 灯火管制开始不久，一个勤务兵顺着列车车身走着，他弄出的嘎拉嘎拉响声惊动了我们。', '名词: orderliness 名词复数: orderlies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prone', '[proʊn]', 'adj.易于 ... 的；有 ... 倾向的；俯卧的', '1. He was prone to anger. 他易于发怒。 2. The child is rather accident-prone. 那个小孩很容易出事儿。 3. People are more prone to make mistakes when they are tired. 人们疲劳时更容易出差错。 4. He\'s probably prone to domestic violence. 他也许有家庭暴力的倾向。', '副词: pronely 名词: proneness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hearing', '[\'hɪrɪŋ]', 'n.听力；听觉；说话或申辩的机会；审讯；听证会 动词hear的现在分词.', '1. He has a good faculty of hearing. 他的听力生来就好。 2. His hearing was impaired after the explosion. 爆炸后他的听力受到了损害。 3. Loud noise would impair your hearing. 大的噪音会损害你的听觉。 4. Vision and hearing are exteroceptive senses. 视觉与听觉都是感受外界刺激的官能。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('body', '[\'bɑːdi]', 'n.身体；主体；正文；主要部分；尸体；躯体；团体 v.赋…以形体', '1. A balanced diet provides nutrition for your body. 均衡的食物使你的身体获得营养。 2. Alcoholic drink can have a bad effect on your body. 含酒精的饮料会对你身体有很坏的影响。 3. He is not mentioned in the main body of the text. 文章的主体中没有提到他。 4. The only part you need to read carefully is the body of your contract. 你只需仔细阅读合同的正文部分。 5. Imagination bodies forth the forms of things unknown. 想象让这些未知事物形状具体。', '名词复数: bodies 过去式: bodied 过去分词: bodied 现在分词: bodying 第三人称单数: bodies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('receive', '[rɪ\'siːv]', 'v.接到；收到；接待', '1. Neither John nor I am to receive the award. 约翰和我谁都不会接到奖赏。 2. I was on vacation last week and didn\'t receive your fax. 上星期我正在度假，没收到你们的传真。 3. He was received as an honoured visitor. 他以贵宾的身分受到款待。', '过去式: received 过去分词: received 现在分词: receiving 第三人称单数: receives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grab', '[ɡræb]', 'v.抓住；攫取 n.抓取物；抓', '1. Grab a seat and make yourself at home. 随便找个地方坐，别客气。 2. Let\'s grab a sandwich and go to see the film. 让我们赶快吃个三明治就去看电影吧。 3. He grabbed my collar and pulled me towards him. 他抓住我的领子把我拉倒他面前。 4. When I gave him the chance, he grabbed it at once. 我给他这一机会，他立刻抓住不放。 5. The job is up for grabs. Why don\'t you apply now? 那工作谁都可以争取。你怎么不现在就申请呢？', '名词: grabber 过去式: grabbed 过去分词: grabbed 现在分词: grabbing 第三人称单数: grabs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('portion', '[\'pɔːrʃn]', 'n.部分；命运；分担的责任；份 v.分配；命运注定', '1. I read a portion of the manuscript. 我读了原稿的一部分。 2. The cake is big enough to be divided into sixteen portions. 这个蛋糕很大,足够分为十六份。 3. He has accepted his portion in life. 他安于天命。 4. Sorrow has always been her portion. 她的命运一直与悲哀相连。', '形容词: portionable 名词: portioner 过去式: portioned 过去分词: portioned 现在分词: portioning 第三人称单数: portions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shoe', '[ʃuː]', 'n.鞋；鞋状物；蹄铁；制动蹄片 vt.穿鞋；装防护物', '1. The shoes are a perfect fit. 这双鞋子穿着非常合脚。 2. My shoe laces have come undone. 我的鞋带松开了。 3. I can feel a nail sticking into my shoe. 我觉得有钉子扎进鞋里。 4. She eased her injured foot into her shoe. 她小心翼翼地把受伤的脚伸进鞋里。 5. I bent over to put my shoe on the other day and fell off the bench. 有一天我弯腰穿鞋时从凳子上摔了下来。', '过去式: shod 过去分词: shod/shodden 现在分词: shoeing 第三人称单数: shoes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kindergarten', '[\'kɪndərɡɑːrtn]', 'n.幼儿园', '1. It is noisy in the kindergarten. 幼儿园里很嘈杂。 2. These children hit it off well in the kindergarten. 这些小孩在幼儿园里相处得很好。 3. The nurse walked the children out of the kindergarten. 保育员把孩子们带出了幼儿园。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('actor', '[\'æktər]', 'n.演员；行动者', '1. The young actor pretended to be Hamlet. 那个年轻演员扮演哈姆雷特。 2. John promises well as an actor. 约翰有希望成为演员。 3. An actor have to learn to laugh off bad review. 演员需学会能对贬斥性评论一笑置之的本事。 4. The star of the film is a previously unknown actor. 这部电影里的明星以前是个默默无闻的演员。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('zebra', '[\'zebrə]', 'n.斑马；斑马线', '1. Seemingly everyone likes the zebra. 似乎每个人都喜欢斑马。 2. The neck of the zebra was nipped by a lion. 狮子咬断了那头斑马的脖子。 3. There was only one big road to cross, but it had a zebra crossing. 只有一条大路要过，但它有斑马线。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('destiny', '[\'destəni]', 'n.命运', '1. Destiny is sometimes cruel. 命运有时是残酷的。 2. Your destiny is interwoven with mine. 你的命运已和我的命运结合在一起了。 3. Some people believe that the Fates preside over man\'s destiny. 有些人相信，命运之神支配人类的命运。', '名词复数: destinies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spin', '[spɪn]', 'v.(使)旋转；疾驰；纺织；结网；眩晕 n.纺织；旋转；眩晕；疾驰', '1. My sister can spin on her toes like a dancer. 我妹妹能像舞者一样踮着脚尖旋转。 2. The motorcycles were spinning along at full speed. 摩托车正全速疾驰。 3. Mother used to spin her own yarn. 母亲过去一直是自己纺纱的。 4. In spring, they spin their cocoons. 到了春天，它们才吐丝结茧。 5. Before the invention of spin technology, zoic fur were mainly material. 在纺织技术尚未发明之前，动物的毛皮是人们服装的主要材料。', '过去式: spun/span 过去分词: spun 现在分词: spinning 第三人称单数: spins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sometime', '[\'sʌmtaɪm]', 'adj.以前的 adv.改天；来日；某时', '1. He is my sometime boss. 他是我从前的上司。 2. Our sometime classmate, Rose, is now a pop star. 我们以前的同学罗斯,现在是明星了。 3. Maybe we can go scuba diving sometime. 也许改天我们能潜泳。 4. I\'d like to drop in and see you sometime next week. 我想在下周什么时候顺便来看看你。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('capitalism', '[\'kæpɪtəlɪzəm]', 'n.资本主义', '1. Capitalism is based on private ownership. 资本主义是建立在私有制基础上的。 2. The essence of his argument is that capitalism cannot succeed. 他的论点的核心是资本主义不能成功。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('optimum', '[\'ɑːptɪməm]', 'adj.最佳的；最适宜的 n.最适宜', '1. The market offers optimum condition for sale. 市场为销售提供了最佳条件。 2. You have established the optimum price. 你已制定了最佳价格。 3. The optimum starting age is ten. 最佳起始年龄是10岁。 4. Now your advice is very optimum. 现在你的建议是很适宜的。 5. Strive for optimum, not maximum, performance. 不求最多、最花哨，只求最适宜。', '名词复数: optima');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('discard', '[dɪs\'kɑːrd]', 'vt.丢弃；抛弃 vi.丢牌 n.丢牌；废牌', '1. He discarded his winter clothing. 他把冬天穿的衣服都丢弃了。 2. My mother-in-law would discard them on the spot. 我的岳母是会当场把它们扔掉的。 3. History discarded him. 他被历史所抛弃。 4. You\'ve got to discard before you can pick up another card. 你得先打出一张牌，才能拿另一张牌。', '形容词: discardable 名词: discarder 过去式: discarded 过去分词: discarded 现在分词: discarding 第三人称单数: discards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conference', '[\'kɒnfərəns]', 'n.会议；讨论会；协商会；会谈', '1. He is in conference. 他正在开会。 2. An international conference will be held in Beijing next month. 一个国际性的会议下月将在北京举行。 3. There will be a banquet following the conference. 会议过后将有一个宴会。 4. We are all fully confident that the conference will be a great success. 我们都有充分的信心,这次会议将会非常成功。', '形容词: conferential');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('saddle', '[\'sædl]', 'n.鞍；车座；山脊；当权 vt.装以马鞍；使负担 vi.装马鞍', '1. The jockey vaulted into the saddle . 骑士一跃而跨坐鞍上。 2. The saddle galled the horse\'s back. 马鞍擦伤了马背。 3. The bicycle saddle is too high for this child. 这辆自行车车座对这孩子来说太高了。 4. He is determined to stay in the saddle at all cost. 他打定主意要不惜一切代价继续掌权。 5. I had to saddle for him the first few times. 头几次我得替他套马鞍。 6. He saddled up his horse and rode away. 他给马装上鞍子便骑马离去了。', '过去式: saddled 过去分词: saddled 现在分词: saddling 第三人称单数: saddles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('toss', '[tɔːs]', 'n.投掷；震荡 v.投掷；摇荡；辗转', '1. The decision depended on the toss of a coin. 那项决定是靠掷硬币的方法做出的。 2. The first toss here would appear to favor Candida. 第一次投掷结果看来对坎迪德有利。 3. The children tossed the ball to each other. 孩子们互相把球扔来扔去。 4. My husband was tossing and turning all night. 我丈夫整夜翻来覆去睡不着。', '名词: tosser 过去式: tossed 过去分词: tossed 现在分词: tossing 第三人称单数: tosses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adapt', '[ə\'dæpt]', 'vt.改编；使适应 vi.适应；适合', '1. This novel has been adapted for radio from the Russian original. 这部小说已由俄文原著改编成无线电广播节目。 2. She adapted herself quickly to the new climate. 她很快就适应了这种新气候。 3. You must adapt to the norms of the society you live in. 在社会中生活就要遵循社会行为准则。 4. It\'s hard to adapt this novel for children. 要将这部小说改编为适合小孩的阅读水准很难。', '过去式: adapted 过去分词: adapted 现在分词: adapting 第三人称单数: adapts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('phone', '[foʊn]', 'n.电话；电话机；听筒；耳机；[语]音素 v.打电话 suf.表示“声音”或“说 ... 语言的人”', '1. What\'s your phone number? 你的电话号码是多少？ 2. I nearly smashed the phone in fury. 盛怒之下，我差点把电话机砸碎。 3. She picked up the phone but didn\'t speak. 她拿起话筒,但并没有说话。 4. I tuned the tone of the stone phone with a bone. 我用骨头调整了石质耳机的音调。', '过去式: phoned 过去分词: phoned 现在分词: phoning 第三人称单数: phones');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('possess', '[pə\'zes]', 'vt.拥有；持有；支配', '1. Different workers possess different skills. 不同的工作者有不同的技能。 2. Rose is a woman who possesses a rare intelligence. 罗丝是一个拥有非凡智慧的女人。 3. The police asked me if I possessed a gun. 警察问我是否有枪。 4. She was possessed by the desire to be rich. 她被致富的欲望所支配。', '名词: possessor 过去式: possessed 过去分词: possessed 现在分词: possessing 第三人称单数: possesses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pose', '[poʊz]', 'v.摆姿势；把...摆正位置；造成；提出；假装 n.姿态；姿势；装腔作势', '1. Please sit still while you pose for your photo. 你摆好姿势拍照时请坐着别动。 2. The artist posed his model carefully. 这个艺术家仔细地把他的模型放好。 3. All the subjects are well posed. 所有的东西都摆好了位置。 4. Pollution poses a threat to the continued existence of this species. 污染对这一物种的继续生存造成了威胁。 5. She always liked to strike a noble pose. 她总是喜欢摆出一副高贵的样子。', '形容词: posable 过去式: posed 过去分词: posed 现在分词: posing 第三人称单数: poses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('automatic', '[ˌɔːtə\'mætɪk]', 'adj.自动的；无意识的；必然的 n.自动装置；半自动武器', '1. This heating system has an automatic temperature control. 这个暖气系统有自动化的温度调节系统。 2. We get an automatic increase in pay every year. 我们的薪金每年会自动增长。 3. For most of us breathing is automatic. 我们大多数人的呼吸都是无意识的。 4. A fine for this offence is automatic. 对于这种过失,罚款是必然的。 5. We now consider it to be the primordial automatic device because it held the first breath of lifelikeness in a machine. 而我们现在之所以把它看成是自动装置的鼻祖，是因为它在一个机器装置中成功地把握到了生命之为生命的第一次呼吸。', '副词: automatically 名词: automaticity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crop', '[krɑːp]', 'n.农作物；收成；庄稼；(一)批 v.修剪；啃吃；收获；出现', '1. The flood did a lot of damage to the crops. 洪水毁坏了大量农作物。 2. We have had the biggest wheat crop ever this year. 今年我们的小麦收获量是有史以来最好的。 3. The crop died due to a lack of rain for 5 months. 5个月没下雨了,庄稼枯死了。 4. The programme brought quite a crop of complaints from viewers. 该节目招致观众诸多不满. 5. She asked the barber to crop her hair short. 她叫理发师把她的头发剪短了。', '过去式: cropped 过去分词: cropped 现在分词: cropping 第三人称单数: crops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('journal', '[\'dʒɜːrnl]', 'n.日志；日记；期刊', '1. He kept a journal during his visit to Japan. 他在访问日本期间坚持记日记。 2. He wrote a journal of his travels. 他写了一本旅行日记。 3. He subscribed to a journal this year. 今年他订了一份期刊。 4. The journal makes its appearance once two months. 这本刊物两个月出版一次。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('frequency', '[\'friːkwənsi]', 'n.频繁；频率', '1. Accidents on that highway are happening with increasing frequency. 那条高速公路上车祸发生得越来越频繁。 2. Accidents are happening with increasing frequency. 事故正在愈加频繁地发生。 3. He wrote to both with tolerable frequency. 他和他们通信，相当频繁。 4. He varied the transmission frequency. 他变换了无线电传送的频率。', '名词复数: frequencies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coordinates', '[kə\'ʊɔːdənəts]', 'n.坐标；相配之衣物 名词coordinate的复数形式.', '1. The Hamiltonian is separable in normal coordinates. 哈密顿在筒子坐标中是可分离的。 2. Compute screen coordinates using viewport settings. 使用视区设置计算屏幕坐标。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('touch', '[tʌtʃ]', 'vt.触摸；感动；吃；喝；触及 vi.接触；联系 n.触觉；接触；修饰；少许；痕迹', '1. Don\'t touch the paint until it\'s dry. 油漆未干,切勿触摸。 2. His sad story touched our hearts. 他的悲惨的故事深深打动了我们的心。 3. I\'m not going to touch a thing tonight. 今天晚上,我什么也不打算吃了。 4. I could use a touch of alcohol in this drink. 我可以在这饮料里喝到些酒。 5. The two wires were touching. 那两条金属线搭在一起了。（《牛津高阶英汉双解词典》） 6. The blind have a keen sense of touch. 盲人有敏锐的触觉。', '形容词: touchable 名词: touchableness 过去式: touched 过去分词: touched 现在分词: touching 第三人称单数: touches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('defend', '[dɪ\'fend]', 'v.防守；防护；辩护', '1. Some players are better at defending. 有些运动员较擅长打防卫。 2. The union said that they would take action to defend their member\'s jobs. 工会说他们将采取行动维护会员的工作权益。 3. He was afraid of being attacked by Liu Bei and Sun Quan, so he sent a troop to defend Jingzhou. 他害怕刘备和孙权继续向他进攻,派人在荆州防守。 4. She demonstrated how best to defend oneself. 她示范最有效的自卫方法。', '形容词: defendable 名词: defender 过去式: defended 过去分词: defended 现在分词: defending 第三人称单数: defends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fifty', '[\'fɪfti]', 'num.五十', '1. He fathered a daughter at the age of fifty. 他五十岁时生下一个女儿。 2. Black smog reduced visibility to about fifty yards. 黑色的烟雾使能见度降到大约五十码左右。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thus', '[ðʌs]', 'adv.这样；如此；因此；从而', '1. Hold the wheel in both hands, thus. 用双手握住方向盘 2. The text runs thus. 原文如此。 3. He forgot to turn on the radio and thus missed the program. 他忘了打开收音机，因此错过了那个节目。 4. The mass production can decrease the cost and thus they can not be so expensive. 大规模生产能降低成本', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('kneel', '[niːl]', 'v.跪', '1. Do not kneel, go straight to your feet. 千万不要跪着，要把脚伸直。 2. Christians often kneel down to say their prayers. 基督教徒通常跪着做祷告。', '过去式: knelt/kneeled 过去分词: knelt/kneeled 现在分词: kneeling 第三人称单数: kneels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('laughter', '[\'læftər]', 'n.【U】笑；笑声', '1. We couldn\'t withhold our laughter. 我们忍不住大笑起来。 2. He gave me a fright by bursting into a sudden laughter. 他突然大笑起来，吓了我一跳。 3. Her funny costume caused much mirthful laughter among the guests. 她那滑稽的服装引得客人哄堂大笑。 4. The room echoed with their happy laughter. 房间里回荡着他们的欢笑声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('junior', '[\'dʒuːniər]', 'adj.资历较浅的；年少的；下级的 n.晚辈；三年级生；年少者；地位较低者', '1. I started the job as a junior secretary. 刚开始这份工作时，我是初级秘书。 2. The president was so young that he was junior to some of his employees. 总裁的年龄甚至是比他的一些雇员还小。 3. He likes to lord it over the junior staff. 他喜欢对下级职员逞威风。 4. She ranks as my junior in the clan. 她的辈分比我小。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('concentrate', '[\'kɑːnsntreɪt]', 'v.专心；集中；浓缩 n.浓缩物', '1. I can\'t concentrate on my work when I\'m tired. 我累了就无法集中精力工作。 2. The confusing matters make him unable to concentrate on his study. 那么多烦心事使他无法专心学习。 3. The crowds concentrated round the palace. 人群汇集在宫殿的四周。 4. Birds concentrate in places where food is abundant. 鸟聚集在食物丰盛的地方。 5. It is an orange concentrate which you dilute with water. 这是一种兑水饮用的浓缩橙汁.', '形容词: concentrative 副词: concentratively 名词: concentrator 过去式: concentrated 过去分词: concentrated 现在分词: concentrating 第三人称单数: concentrates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expand', '[ɪk\'spænd]', 'v.使 ... 膨胀；详述；扩张；增加；张开', '1. Metals expand when they are heated. 金属遇热则膨胀。 2. Would you expand upon the matter a little further? 请你再进一步谈谈这件事好吗? 3. They conferred on the best way to expand business. 他们商议扩展业务的最好方法。 4. Our foreign trade has expanded during recent years. 近年来我们的对外贸易有所增加。', '形容词: expandable 名词: expander 过去式: expanded 过去分词: expanded 现在分词: expanding 第三人称单数: expands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('administration', '[ədˌmɪnɪ\'streɪʃn]', 'n.实施；管理；行政；行政部门；任期', '1. He is responsible for the administration of justice. 他负责赏罚。 2. He works in hospital administration. 他从事医院管理工作. 3. The company developed rapidly under his administration. 在他的管理下，公司发展得很快。 4. Head teachers are more involved in administration than in teaching. 校长的行政工作比教学工作多。', '形容词: administrative 副词: administratively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prisoner', '[\'prɪznər]', 'n.囚犯', '1. The prisoner made a plea for mercy. 囚犯恳求宽恕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('embrace', '[ɪm\'breɪs]', 'v.拥抱；包含；包围；接受；信奉 n.拥抱', '1. We embraced each other. 我们互相拥抱。 2. She held out her arms to embrace the little girl. 她伸出双臂来拥抱那个小女孩。 3. Many subjects are embraced in an encyclopedia. 百科全书中包含许多科目。 4. We allowed the warm water to embrace us. 我们让温水包围我们 5. He enfolded the child in an affectionate embrace. 他疼爱得把孩子紧紧搂在怀里。', '形容词: embraceable 名词: embracement 过去式: embraced 过去分词: embraced 现在分词: embracing 第三人称单数: embraces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anniversary', '[ˌænɪ\'vɜːrsəri]', 'n.周年纪念；周年纪念日', '1. He gave me a necklace as an anniversary gift. 他给我一条项链作为周年纪念礼物。 2. They held a dinner to celebrate his anniversary. 为了庆祝他的周年纪念他们举办了一个宴会。 3. How did you celebrate your wedding anniversary? 你是怎样庆祝结婚周年纪念日的？ 4. She reproached her husband for having forgotten their wedding anniversary. 她责怪丈夫忘了他们的结婚周年纪念日。', '名词复数: anniversaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abound', '[ə\'baʊnd]', 'v.富于；充满', '1. Most of her poems abound in imagery. 她的诗歌大多数富于形象。 2. The myths and traditions of India abound with references. 印度神话和传统充满了参考价值。 3. A very different world will abound as this comes to be so. 一个非常不同的世界将充满着这一切，当这实现。', '过去式: abounded 过去分词: abounded 现在分词: abounding 第三人称单数: abounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('counterpart', '[\'kaʊntərpɑːrt]', 'n.职务相当的人；对应物；相似之物；副本', '1. The secretary of state is the counterpart of the foreign minister. 国务卿相当于外交部长。 2. The sale director phoned her counterpart in the other firm. 这位销售主任给另一家公司的销售主任打电话。 3. Night is the counterpart of day. 黑夜与白天相辅相成。 4. I racked my memory in vain for its counterpart in literature: perhaps you could think of one. 我绞尽脑汁也想不出它在文学中的对等物，也许你可以想出一个。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coherent', '[koʊ\'hɪrənt]', 'adj.连贯的；有条理的；一致的；粘着的', '1. He welded their stories into a single coherent account. 他把他们的故事连在一起写成一个连贯的报导。 2. The subjects of the curriculum form a coherent whole. 课程中的科目构成了一个连贯的整体。 3. She only became coherent again two hours after the attack. 她发病两小时之后才恢复了清楚地说话的能力。 4. She had felt there was something wrong, but couldn\'t give coherent reasons. 她感到有些不对头，但是讲不清楚理由。', '副词: coherently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tragic', '[\'trædʒɪk]', 'adj.悲剧的；悲惨的', '1. This delay was to have tragic results. 这样的延误即将导致悲剧的结局。 2. I don\'t like the tragic ending of the film. 我不喜欢电影悲剧的结尾。 3. Her tragic story touched us all deeply/touched our hearts with sorrow. 她的经历很悲惨，我们都深受感动[我们都很伤心]。 4. She listened to the tragic news ashen-faced. 她听到这一悲惨消息，脸都白了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('available', '[ə\'veɪləbl]', 'adj.可利用的；可得到的；有空的；有效的；<贬>【政】有资格的，适合的', '1. Do you have a room available? 你们有空房间吗？ 2. The swimming pool is available only in summer. 这个游泳池只在夏天开放。 3. All sorts of lamps are available in that shop. 在那家商店可买到各式各样的灯具。 4. The Prime Minister was not available for comment. 首相无暇作出评论。', '副词: availably 名词: availability');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('earth', '[ɜːrθ]', 'n.地球；泥土；世间', '1. The moon goes round the earth. 月亮绕着地球转。 2. What percentage of the earth is covered by oceans? 地球上百分之多少被海水覆盖着？ 3. He dived his hand into the earth. 他将手插入泥土中。 4. The machine cast up a big heap of earth. 机器卷起了一大堆泥土。', '过去式: earthed 过去分词: earthed 现在分词: earthing 第三人称单数: earths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('secure', '[sə\'kjʊr]', 'adj.安全的；牢靠的；稳妥的 vt.使安全；获得；固定', '1. If you are not sure it is secure, do not debug it. 如果您不能确定它是安全的,请不要调试它。 2. His place in history is now secure. 他在历史上的地位现在已经稳固了。 3. A climber needs secure footholds. 攀登的人脚踩的地方要很牢固。 4. We must create a secure and reliable international environment of lasting peace and stability. 我们要创造安全可靠、长期稳定的国际和平环境。 5. Some measures are needed to secure the farmland against shift sand. 需要采取措施使农田免遭流沙的侵袭。', '形容词: securable 副词: securely 比较级: securer 最高级: securest 名词: securement 过去式: secured 过去分词: secured 现在分词: securing 第三人称单数: secures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cancel', '[\'kænsl]', 'v.取消；作废；注销；抵消；删除 n.取消；删除', '1. The match had to be cancelled due to the bad weather. 比赛因天气不好只得取消。 2. If the worst comes to the worst, we\'ll have to cancel our holiday plans. 要是情况不妙，我们就只好取消度假计划了。 3. I\'ve lost my crdit card, so I have to go to the bank to cancel it. 我的信用卡弄丢了,我得去银行申请作废。 4. The ticket shall be cancelled once you enter the cinema. 你一进入电影院后,这张票就得注销了。', '形容词: cancelable 名词: canceler 过去式: canceled/cancelled 过去分词: canceled/cancelled 现在分词: canceling/cancelling 第三人称单数: cancels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forest', '[\'fɔːrɪst]', 'n.森林；林火 vt.(用树林)覆盖；置于(树林中)', '1. He went to the forest on horseback. 他骑马去森林了。 2. The deer escaped to the deep forest. 那鹿逃入了丛林深处。 3. There is a pine forest near our house. 我们家附近有片松树林。 4. Thousands of old trees were lost in the forest fire. 成千上万棵老树在森林大火中被烧毁。 5. He wants to forest a pasture with pine trees. 他想在牧场上种植松树造林。', '形容词: forestal 名词: forestation 过去式: forested 过去分词: forested 现在分词: foresting 第三人称单数: forests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('host', '[hoʊst]', 'n.主人；主持人；主办方；大量；寄主；主机 v.主办；主持；做东', '1. At the end of the party, we thanked our host and went back home. 宴会结束时,我们谢了主人后便回家去了。 2. He was the host for a TV talk show. 他是一名电视脱口秀的主持人。 3. Which country will be the host country for the next Olympic Games? 哪个国家将是下届奥运会的主办国？ 4. A host of friends met him at the railway station. 一大群朋友在火车站迎接他。 5. We sincerely wish China success in hosting Expo 2010. 我们衷心祝愿中国成功主办2010年世博会。', '形容词: hostly 过去式: hosted 过去分词: hosted 现在分词: hosting 第三人称单数: hosts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('size', '[saɪz]', 'n.大小；规模；尺寸；尺码；浆料；胶料 v.按大小排列(或分类)；给…上胶 adj.（用于复合词）…大小的', '1. The size of the apples varied. 那些苹果大小不同。 2. The company doubled its size in nine years. 9年来这家公司的规模扩大了一倍。 3. What size of collar is this shirt? 这衬衣领子的尺寸是多少？ 4. Do you have the same size and design in black? 这种尺码和款式有黑色的吗? 5. A man\'s shirt is sized by its neck. 男子的衬衫号码是按领口大小分的。', '名词: sizer 过去式: sized 过去分词: sized 现在分词: sizing 第三人称单数: sizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('timid', '[\'tɪmɪd]', 'adj.胆怯的；害羞的', '1. They taunted him for being timid. 他们讥笑他胆小。 2. He is as timid as a sheep. 他像绵羊一样怯懦。 3. The least noise would startle the timid child. 最小的响声也会吓着这个胆小的孩子的。 4. He is a timid boy; it\'s impossible for him to brawl with anyone. 他是一个胆小的男孩，他不可能和任何人吵架。', '副词: timidly 比较级: timider 最高级: timidest 名词: timidity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adverb', '[\'ædvɜːb]', 'n.副词 adj.副词的', '1. You should run on an adverb to the verb. 你应在这动词后附加一个副词。 2. The adverb is a kind of form word, which has a modifying function. 副词属于虚辞，有修饰的作用。 3. Fill in each blank with the adjective or the adverb given in its proper degree. 用所给形容词或副词的适当形式填空。 4. In Chinese, the classification of the auxiliary verb and the adverb always have dispute. 摘要汉语中助动词和副词的分类一直有争议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contemplate', '[\'kɑːntəmpleɪt]', 'vt.注视；沉思；打算', '1. He stood contemplating the painting. 他站着审视那幅图画。 2. It terrified me to contemplate the consequence of your action. 一想到你行动的后果,我就感到害怕。 3. The doctor contemplated the difficult operation he had to perform. 医生细想他要进行的棘手的手术。 4. We contemplate obtaining a technical license. 我们希望获得一项技术许可证。', '名词: contemplator 过去式: contemplated 过去分词: contemplated 现在分词: contemplating 第三人称单数: contemplates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('insure', '[ɪn\'ʃʊr]', 'vt.保险；确保 vi.买保险', '1. I want to insure my residence. 我要为自己的住宅保险。 2. I\'d like to insure this package for 50 dollars. 我想要这包东西保险50美元。 3. I am insured for all risks. 我给自己保了综合险。 4. My house is insured against fire. 我的房子保了火险。 5. You\'ll insure with the People\'s Insurance Company of China. I presume? 我想你们是在中国人民保险公司投保的吧。', '形容词: insurable 名词: insurability 过去式: insured 过去分词: insured 现在分词: insuring 第三人称单数: insures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slogan', '[\'sloʊɡən]', 'n.口号；标语', '1. The advertising slogan was a play on words. 那条广告口号是双关语。 2. A slogan is over the blackboard. 一条标语在黑板正上方。 3. He daubed the wall with a slogan. 他在墙上写了一条标语。 4. A product will sell better if it is promoted with a slogan. 如果用标语促销,产品的销势会更好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('report', '[rɪ\'pɔːrt]', 'n.报告；传闻；成绩单；爆炸声 v.报告；报导；叙述；举报；报到；对…负责', '1. He is reading a report of the state of the roads. 他正在看一篇关于道路状况的报告。 2. I have only reports to go on. 我的依据只是谣传而已。 3. My son got an excellent report last semester. 我儿子上学期成绩出色。 4. The tyre burst with a loud report. 轮胎砰的一声巨响爆裂了。 5. I shall have to report this to the authorities. 我得把这事向当局报告。', '形容词: reportable 过去式: reported 过去分词: reported 现在分词: reporting 第三人称单数: reports');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sunrise', '[\'sʌnraɪz]', 'n.【U】日出 n.【C】(太阳升起时的)一片天空', '1. The beauty of the sunrise is beyond description. 日出的美景难以描述。 2. The sunrise seen from high in the mountains was a tremendous spectacle. 从山上居高远望，日出景象蔚为奇观。 3. The town gardens are open to the public from sunrise to the sunset daily. 市立公园每天从早到晚对公众开放。 4. There was a glorious sunrise over the mountains. 山上呈现出一片美轮美奂的天空。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('parcel', '[\'pɑːrsl]', 'n.包裹；部分；一块(土地) vt.分配；打包', '1. He snipped the string and untied the parcel. 他剪断绳子，解开包裹。 2. He tied the parcel with twine. 他用细绳来捆扎包裹。 3. Her stinginess is part and parcel of her nature. 她生性吝啬。 4. Once you\'ve explored a bit, perhaps you\'ll find a perfect parcel of land to build your house or business. 一旦你开始探险，你可能会找到一块理想的土地去建造你的房子或者发展你的商业。 5. He used to parcel out jobs to representatives. 他曾将工作分配各个代表。', '过去式: parceled/parcelled 过去分词: parceled/parcelled 现在分词: parceling/parcelling 第三人称单数: parcels/parcels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brow', '[braʊ]', 'n.前额；眉毛；山脊；表情', '1. The nurse mopped his fevered brow. 护士擦拭了他发烫的前额。 2. Deep furrows lined his brow. 深深的皱纹布上他的额头。 3. His brows went up in surprise. 他惊讶地竖起了眉毛。 4. His brow corrugated with the effort of thinking. 他皱着眉头用心地思考。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tomb', '[tuːm]', 'n.坟墓 vt.埋葬', '1. Those dead soldiers were buried in the tombs. 那些死去的战士被埋葬在坟墓里。 2. A tombstone stands in front of her tomb. 她墓前立着一块墓碑。 3. A group of student placed a wreath at the tomb of the national hero. 一群学生在那位民族英雄墓前献上花圈。 4. The archaeologist researched into the tombs of many of England\'s literary great. 这位考古学家对许多英国文坛宗师的坟墓进行了研究。 5. In the opening verse we find the women coming to the tomb to anoint the body for burial. 在本章一开始的经节中，我们看到一些妇女来到坟墓前，为埋葬耶稣用油膏耶稣的身体。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inertia', '[ɪ\'nɜːrʃə]', 'n.惯性；惰性', '1. Inertia carried the car to the pavement. 惯性使汽车驶到了人行道上。 2. Inertia is evident in our every day experiences. 惯性在我们日常生活中是很常见的。 3. Everyone has his psychological inertia, or in some way, indolence. 每个人都有一种思维惯性或者说惰性。 4. Because of the sheer inertia of the system many badly needed reform is never introduced. 纯粹是由於制度本身有惰性，很多事急需改革却从未实行。', '形容词: inertial 副词: inertially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('current', '[\'kɜːrənt]', 'n.趋势；(水、气、电)流 adj.现在的；流通的', '1. Nothing disturbs the peaceful current of life in the village. 没有任何事干扰村里一向平静的生活. 2. The block becomes magnetic when the current is switched on. 通电时线圈即具磁性。 3. The current is deep and strong down the stream. 下游的水又深又急。 4. The current trend is towards informal clothing. 目前的趋势是穿着比较随便。', '副词: currently 名词: currentness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attempt', '[ə\'tempt]', 'v.企图；尝试 n.企图；试图', '1. He attempted to smother up the scandal about his family. 他企图掩饰有关他家庭的丑闻。 2. I would be the last to attempt to answer the question. 我是最不可能去尝试回答这个问题。 3. The enemy failed in their attempt to land on the island. 敌人在岛上登陆的企图失败了。 4. He studied hard in an attempt to pass the exam. 他努力学习试图通过考试。', '形容词: attemptable 名词: attempter 过去式: attempted 过去分词: attempted 现在分词: attempting 第三人称单数: attempts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stale', '[steɪl]', 'adj.不新鲜的；陈腐的；厌倦的 v.变得不新鲜；腐坏；(动物)撒尿 n.(动物的)尿', '1. His hunger makes his stale bread go down. 饥饿使他把这不新鲜的面包吞了下去。 2. He always bought two loaves of stale bread. 他总是要买两个不新鲜的面包。 3. The males think the females have talent for telling stale tales. 男人认为女人有讲陈腐故事的才能。 4. After ten years in the job, she felt stale and needed a change. 在那个岗位干了十年之后，她觉得腻了，需要换换工作。 5. The pleasure I get from playing guitar never stales. 我对吉它一直兴味盎然。', '副词: stalely 比较级: staler 最高级: stalest 名词: staleness 过去式: staled 过去分词: staled 现在分词: staling 第三人称单数: stales');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plausible', '[\'plɔːzəbl]', 'adj.似真实合理的；动听的；看起来有道理的，貌似可信的', '1. Such a theory seems very plausible. 这一理论貌似十分有理。 2. He can not find a plausible reason for his absence. 翻译他找不到缺席的合理理由。 3. Though controversial, it is plausible. 虽有争议，却似乎行得通。 4. He trotted out a most plausible story, but most of us were inclined to doubt the truth of it. 他提出了一个听起来很有道理的说法，但我们大多数人对此都持怀疑态度。', '副词: plausibly 名词: plausibility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('programme', '[\'proʊɡræm]', 'n.方案；（活动的）程序；节目；规划；课程；（机器工作的）程序 v.计划；培养；编程；制作节目；预设', '1. The government has initiated a programme of economic reform. 政府已开始实施经济改革方案。 2. We now have a new Quality Assurance programme. 我们现在用的是一套新的质保程序。 3. The news programme overran the allotted time. 新闻节目超出了规定的时间。 4. The purpose of the programme is primarily educational. 演出该节目的主要目的是为了进行教育。 5. The final section of road is programmed for completion next month. 最后一段道路计划于下月竣工。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('locate', '[\'loʊkeɪt]', 'vt.找出；把 ... 设置在；使坐落于 vi.住下来', '1. The general tried to locate the enemy\'s camp. 那位将军想找出敌人营地的位置。 2. They decided to locate a new school in the suburbs. 他们决定在郊区设置一所新学校。 3. The company wished to locate its new factory beside the river. 这家公司希望把新工厂建在河边。 4. After he retired, he went to locate in California. 他退休后在加里弗尼亚定居。', '形容词: locatable 名词: locater 过去式: located 过去分词: located 现在分词: locating 第三人称单数: locates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bath', '[bæθ]', 'n.洗澡；浴室；沐浴；浴盆 v.洗澡 Bath. n.巴斯(英国城市)', '1. He takes a cold bath every day. 他每天洗一个冷水澡。 2. The idea came to him in his bath. 他洗澡时想出了这个主意。 3. I want a double room with a bath. 我要一间有浴室的双人房。 4. After the bath, he took a walk in the yard. 沐浴后，他在院子里散步。 5. It\'s your turn to bath the baby. 轮到你给婴儿洗澡了。 6. He was decorated with the Order of the Bath. 他被授以巴斯勋章。', '名词复数: baths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hemisphere', '[\'hemɪsfɪr]', 'n.半球', '1. the party out ofoffice 2. If you cut a round fruit into two, each half is a hemisphere. 如果你把一个圆的水果切成两半，每一半就是一个半球。 3. The Northern Hemisphere is the part of the world north of the equator, and the Southern Hemisphere is south of the equator. 北半球是地球赤道以北的部分，南半球是赤道以南的部分。', '形容词: hemispheric 副词: hemispherically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stream', '[striːm]', 'n.(小)河；水流；(人；车；气)流；组 v.流动；流出；飘动；将(学生)按能力分组', '1. On either bank of the stream stand rows of willow trees. 小河两岸柳树成行。 2. Sand and leaves trapped the water in the stream. 沙子和树叶堵住了小河的水流。 3. Visitors to the exhibition came in an endless stream. 参观展览会的人络绎不绝。 4. Cars stream along the highway. 汽车在公路上流水般地行驶。', '形容词: streamy 过去式: streamed 过去分词: streamed 现在分词: streaming 第三人称单数: streams');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recede', '[rɪ\'siːd]', 'vi.后退；减弱 vt.撤回', '1. His hair is beginning to recede from his forehead. 他的头发开始从前额往后秃了。 2. As the tide receded we were able to look for shells. 潮水退去，我们就能寻找贝壳了。 3. The prospect of bankruptcy has now receded. 破产的危险已经减少了。 4. Eventually the danger began to recede. 这种危险终于开始减轻。 5. The company decided to recede from a bargain. 公司决定撤销买卖合同。', '过去式: receded 过去分词: receded 现在分词: receding 第三人称单数: recedes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('engineer', '[ˌendʒɪ\'nɪr]', 'n.工程师；机(械)师 vt.设计；建造；策划', '1. Hs is a civil engineer. 他是位土木工程师。 2. His dream is to become an engineer. 他的梦想是将来成为一名工程师。 3. He is a locomotive engineer. 他是一名火车司机。 4. The road is very well engineered. 这条路设计得很好。', '过去式: engineered 过去分词: engineered 现在分词: engineering 第三人称单数: engineers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('consequence', '[\'kɑːnsəkwens]', 'n.结果；后果；重要性；影响', '1. It terrified me to contemplate the consequence of your action. 一想到你行动的后果,我就感到害怕。 2. He studied hard, and in consequence he passed the exam. 他努力学习，因此通过了考试。 3. Happiness is not a reward it is a consequence. 幸福不是报偿，而是结果。 4. In consequence of his bad conduct he was dismissed. 由于行为不良，他被开除了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('talk', '[tɔːk]', 'v.交谈；商讨；演讲；阐述；劝服 n.谈话；会谈；讨论；讲话；空谈', '1. I wish to talk with you in private. 我希望能私下里同你谈话。 2. We need to hold another meeting next week to talk about some technical problems. 我们需要在下周再举行一次会议,来讨论一些技术性的问题。 3. In the hall a woman was talking on diet and health. 在那个大厅里,一名女性正在就饮食与健康发表演讲。 4. He went on to talk about the world situation at present. 他接着又阐述了当期的世界形势。 5. I had a long talk with her that night. 那天晚上,我和她秉烛长谈。', '过去式: talked 过去分词: talked 现在分词: talking 第三人称单数: talks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bandage', '[\'bændɪdʒ]', 'n.绷带 vt.用绷带包扎', '1. The nurse eased away the bandage from the wound. 护士小心翼翼地解开伤口处的绷带。 2. I twisted the bandage round her knee. 我用带缠住了她的膝盖。 3. The waitress put a bandage round his hand. 女服务员用绷带将他的手包扎起来。 4. The surgeon bandaged up his injured head. 外科医生把他受伤的头部包扎起来。', '名词: bandager 过去式: bandaged 过去分词: bandaged 现在分词: bandaging 第三人称单数: bandages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('respect', '[rɪ\'spekt]', 'vt.尊敬；尊重；遵守；关于；涉及 n.尊敬；敬重；关系；方面 n.（复）respects: 敬意；问候', '1. All students should respect their teachers. 凡是学生就应当尊敬老师。 2. I respected their moral standards. 我尊重他们的道德标准。 3. I respect him as a writer and as a man. 我尊重他这位作家，也尊重他这个人。 4. We must respect the laws of a country we are in. 我们必须遵守所在国家的法律。 5. The students have great respect for their history teacher. 学生们非常尊敬他们的历史老师。 6. We called to pay our respects. 我们去拜望了，以表示敬意', '名词: respecter 过去式: respected 过去分词: respected 现在分词: respecting 第三人称单数: respects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('saving', '[\'seɪvɪŋ]', 'n. 节约； 挽救 （复数)savings:储蓄金； 存款 prep. 除 ... 之外 conj. 除了； 除去 save的现在分词', '1. A saving of 30% is obtainable under this scheme. 按这一计划做可以获得百分之三十的节约率。 2. We must work out a better method of saving paper. 我们必须想出更好的节约纸张的方法。 3. They have thought out the effective saving. 他们已想出挽救的办法。 4. He took the chance of losing his life in saving the drowning child. 他冒着生命危险去挽救那个落入水中的小孩。 5. I would like to open a saving account. 我想开活期存款户。 6. It was debated whether saving grace could be obtained outside the membership of the church. 人们在争论除了加入教会之外还有没有其它好处。 7. Apart from saving you time, it also brings in a world of information and knowledge and acquaints you with the latest happenings in your fields of interest. 除了能够为你节省时间，它也能将你带入到一个信息和知识的世界，它能让你接触到你所感兴趣领域里最新的信息。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wheat', '[wiːt]', 'n.小麦；小麦色', '1. This old man is a leading authority on wheat diseases. 这位老人是小麦病虫害方面的权威。 2. This machine crushes wheat grain to make flour. 这台机器把麦子磨成面粉。 3. Wheat is transported from the farms to the mills. 把小麦从农场运到面粉厂。 4. The wheat rippled in the breeze. 小麦在微风中起伏波动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('microphone', '[\'maɪkrəfoʊn]', 'n.麦克风；扩音器', '1. He is talking into a microphone. 他正在对着麦克风讲话。 2. Plug in the microphone or no one will hear me. 请把麦克风插上，不然没人听得到我的声音。 3. He gave a tap at the microphone before speaking. 他在讲话前先轻叩了一下扩音器。 4. You can use a microphone to record words so you can practice your weekly spelling. 用者可使用扩音器去录下字句，以便能于每星期练习串字。', '形容词: microphonic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('couple', '[\'kʌpl]', 'n.对；夫妇；数个 v.连结；交配', '1. They are a nice couple. 他们是很美满的一对。 2. The couple seemed to be on cloud nine. 那对夫妇看上去极其幸福。 3. Next door to us there\'s a couple from the USA. 我们隔壁住著来自美国的一对夫妇。 4. My tourist visa lets me stay for a couple of weeks. 我的观光签证可让我停留数周。 5. They coupled the carriages of the train together. 他们把火车的车厢连接好。', '过去式: coupled 过去分词: coupled 现在分词: coupling 第三人称单数: couples');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expedition', '[ˌekspə\'dɪʃn]', 'n.远征；探险队；迅速', '1. They equipped themselves for the expedition. 他们为远征治装。 2. They planned to organize a scientific expedition. 他们计划组织一次科学考察。 3. He is the commander of the expedition. 他是探险队的队长。 4. The expedition suffered all the rigors of a Canadian winter. 这支探险队饱受了加拿大严冬的折磨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diffuse', '[dɪ\'fjuːz]', 'vt.扩散；散开；传播 vi.弥漫；扩散 adj.冗长的；四散的', '1. The problem is how to diffuse power without creating anarchy. 问题在于如何将权力分散而不造成无政府状态。 2. Fashion trends diffuse themselves rapidly around the globe. 时装新潮很快就在全世界流行起来。 3. The roses diffuse the scent to the air miles around. 玫瑰花的香味儿弥漫在几英里的空气中。 4. He resolved to diffuse the special knowledge that he possessed. 他决心要传播他所具有的特别的知识。 5. Around the cluster is a huge vague diffuse nebulae. 围绕该星团的是一个巨大的模糊的弥漫星云。 6. Professor Smith cut off their diffuse speech and agreed to help them. 史密斯教授打断他们冗长的演讲,答应帮助他们。', '副词: diffusely 名词: diffuseness 过去式: diffused 过去分词: diffused 现在分词: diffusing 第三人称单数: diffuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('manuscript', '[\'mænjuskrɪpt]', 'n.手稿；原稿 adj.手抄的', '1. I read his novel in manuscript. 我看过他小说的手稿。 2. The illumination of the manuscript is delicate. 这个手稿的装饰很精致。 3. The manuscript requires an expert to understand it. 这份手稿只有专家才看得懂。 4. He revised the manuscript of his book before sending it to the publisher. 他对自己那本书的手稿先进行校订，然后才把它交给出版社。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remind', '[rɪ\'maɪnd]', 'vt.使想起；提醒', '1. This story reminds me of my childhood. 这个故事让我想起了我的童年。 2. I feel it is absolutely necessary for me to remind him of the meeting today. 我觉得绝对有必要提醒他今天要开会。', '名词: reminder 过去式: reminded 过去分词: reminded 现在分词: reminding 第三人称单数: reminds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('swallow', '[\'swɑːloʊ]', 'n.燕子；吞咽；一次吞咽的量 v.忍受；吞下；咽下；轻信；不流露感情；收回', '1. There are many swallows flying in the sky. 天空中有许多燕子。 2. The swallow has made a nest under our eaves. 燕子在我们的屋檐下垒了一个窝。 3. He downed the medicine at one swallow. 他一口便把药全吞下了。 4. Let me take a swallow of beer. 让我喝口啤酒。 5. They can\'t treat me like that; I\'m not going to swallow it. 他们不能这样对待我，我忍不下这口气。', '名词: swallower 过去式: swallowed 过去分词: swallowed 现在分词: swallowing 第三人称单数: swallows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disposition', '[ˌdɪspə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.性情；倾向；安排；处置；控制；[计算机] 配置情况', '1. She has a calm and introverted disposition. 她性格文静内向。 2. Joanna had a gentle retiring disposition. 乔安娜性格温柔而腼腆。 3. The child had a placid disposition. 这个孩子性情温和。 4. They showed a disposition to sign the contract. 他们表示有签订合同的意愿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('toll', '[toʊl]', 'n.伤亡人数；钟声；通行费；代价 v.敲钟', '1. The death toll mounted (to 100). 死亡人数上升(至100). 2. The government tried to keep the death toll at a lower level. 政府力图将死亡人数控制在较低标准。 3. We heard the toll of the church bells. 我们听到了教堂大钟传来的钟声。 4. When you hear the bells toll, you\'ll know I\'m not far. 当你听到钟声，就说明我已经在附近了。 5. The church bell tolled the hour. 教堂的鸣钟报时。', '过去式: tolled 过去分词: tolled 现在分词: tolling 第三人称单数: tolls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('handle', '[\'hændl]', 'v.处理；对待；操作；触；买卖 n.把手；柄', '1. I was impressed by her handling of the affair. 我觉得她对此事的处理很了不起。 2. The speaker was roughly handled by the mob. 演说者受到暴民的粗暴对待。 3. He\'s not a very good teacher---he doesn\'t know how to handle children. 他不是一个好的老师---他不懂得如何对待孩子。 4. He knows how to handle the machine. 他会操作这台机器。 5. I turned the handle and opened the door. 我转了转拉手,把门打开。', '形容词: handleless 过去式: handled 过去分词: handled 现在分词: handling 第三人称单数: handles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('undertake', '[ˌʌndər\'teɪk]', 'v.承担；从事；保证；答应', '1. We could undertake the work for the time being. 我们可暂时承担这项工作。 2. We shall undertake the construction of this bridge. 我们将负责这座桥的修建工程。 3. Whatever I may undertake in the coming years, I don\'t need your help. 未来无论我从事什么,我都不需要你的帮助。 4. I can not undertake that you will make a profit. 我不能保证你会获利。', '过去式: undertook 过去分词: undertaken 现在分词: undertaking 第三人称单数: undertakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fireman', '[\'faɪərmən]', 'n.消防队员；司炉工', '1. A brave fireman rescued the woman. 一个勇敢的消防队员救了这女人。 2. The well-trained fireman can get over this tall wall easily. 受过严格训练的消防员可以轻而易举地越过这道高墙。 3. The fireman smashed the door down to reach the children. 消防员破门而入冲向孩子们。 4. A cab was provided for driver and fireman, as in normal railway practice. 按通常的铁路惯例,机车备有司机和司炉工。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fore', '[fɔːr]', 'adj.在前的 n.前头；船头', '1. Her seat is in the fore part of the aircraft. 她的座位在飞机前部。 2. Most modern yachts have a fore and aft rig, but the old galleons were squared-rigged. 大多数现代化游艇配备的都是前后帆，而老式大帆船装的却是横帆。 3. He was ready to charge to the fore for the defence of our motherland. 他随时准备冲在前头来保卫祖国。 4. He come to the fore as a physicist at an early age. 他在早年就成了杰出的物理学家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soccer', '[\'sɑːkər]', 'n.足球，英式足球', '1. People love to play soccer. 人们喜欢踢足球。 2. The boy who is speaking to Helen enjoys playing soccer. 正在跟海伦谈话的那男孩喜爱踢足球。 3. The Government intends to clamp down on soccer hooliganism. 政府拟采取措施严禁在足球比赛中闹事。 4. In soccer, only the goal-keeper may play the ball with his hands. 在足球运动中只有守门员可以用手触球。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('duration', '[du\'reɪʃn]', 'n.持续时间；期间', '1. The duration of the movie is 110 minutes. 这部电影的持续时间是110分钟。 2. He finished the work of three years\' duration. 他用三年的时间完成了这项工作。 3. The duration of marriage is related most obviously to the expectation of life. 很明显，婚姻生活的持续时间与人的预期寿命有关。 4. Well, I\'m stuck here for the duration. 哎，这段时间我只得呆在这儿了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comedy', '[\'kɑːmədi]', 'n.喜剧；滑稽；幽默事件', '1. This comedy has had them rolling in the aisles for two weeks. 这出喜剧让观众们连续两个星期乐得前仰后合。 2. I prefer comedy to tragedy. 我喜欢喜剧而不喜欢悲剧。 3. The drama may be termed a comedy. 这部戏剧可称为喜剧。 4. Who could resist the comedy of American names? 谁能看到美国那些滑稽的地名而不发笑呢?', '名词复数: comedies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fire', '[\'faɪər]', 'n.火；失火；炉火；开火；热情 v.开火；解雇；点燃；急速地连续说', '1. The fire flared up as I put more firewood on it. 我加上了几块木柴, 火顿时旺起来。 2. The house is on fire! 房子着火了！ 3. A cigarette thrown into the woods in dry weather may start a fire. 在天气干燥时把点燃的香烟扔进树林可能会引起火灾。 4. She curled up in front of the fire with a book. 她蜷曲在炉火前看书。 5. She fired her gun at them. 她用枪向他们射击。', '形容词: fireable 名词: firer 过去式: fired 过去分词: fired 现在分词: firing 第三人称单数: fires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shrink', '[ʃrɪŋk]', 'vi.收缩；退缩；萎缩；畏惧，害怕 vt.使收缩 n.收缩；萎缩 n.精神科医生', '1. Will this woolen sweater shrink when washed? 这件羊毛衫洗后会缩水吗？ 2. The company\'s profit margins shrank from 32.5% to 17%. 该公司的边际利润率从32.5%降到了17%。 3. We will never shrink from difficulties. 我们在困难面前决不退缩。 4. The economy is shrinking instead of growing. 经济正在萎缩而不是在增长中。 5. The hot water shrank my pullover. 我的套头毛衣遇热水后收缩了。 6. You can expect some shrink when the jeans are washed. 这种牛仔裤洗后要缩些水。 7. My aunt saw this shrink after her divorce. 我阿姨在离婚后去见过这位心理医生。', '形容词: shrinkable 名词: shrinker 过去式: shrank/shrunk 过去分词: shrunk/shrunken 现在分词: shrinking 第三人称单数: shrinks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('occurrence', '[ə\'kɜːrəns]', 'n.发生；事件；出现', '1. Unfortunately, computer errors are a common occurrence. 不幸的是,计算机错误常常发生。 2. Riots are of frequent occurrence in this province. 这省经常发生骚乱。 3. It is more a made-up story than a real occurrence. 那是杜撰的故事，而不是真实发生的事情。 4. This is a rare occurrence as our climate seldom goes to extremes. 由于这里的气候很少出现极端，所以这是很罕见的情况。', '形容词: occurrent');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('listen', '[\'lɪsn]', 'v.听；倾听；听从；听信 n.听；倾听', '1. She is listening to the radio. 她在听收音机。 2. It is boring to listen to the same story. 听相同的故事是令人厌烦的。 3. He should listen to his intimate feelings. 人应当倾听自己的内心感觉。 4. He refused to listen to the old man\'s counsel. 他拒不听从老人的忠告。', '名词: listener 过去式: listened 过去分词: listened 现在分词: listening 第三人称单数: listens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eleven', '[ɪ\'levn]', 'n.十一；十一个一组 adj.十一的 pron.十一个', '1. The meeting broke up at eleven o\'clock. 会议在十一点钟散会。 2. Mr Hood said that he would have to go on, as he was due at a meeting at eleven o\'clock. 胡德先生说由于他11点钟要出席一个会议，得先走一步了。 3. Not until eleven o\'clock did he come home. 他到十一点才回家。 4. I have received eleven Christmas cards by now. 到现在为止，我已经收到了十一张圣诞卡片。 5. The little boy left primary school at eleven. 这个小男孩十一岁时小学毕业。 6. There are eleven in the room. 屋里有十一个人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wicked', '[\'wɪkɪd]', 'adj.坏的；邪恶的；缺德的 adv.极端地；非常地 vt.吸收', '1. He had a wicked glint in his eyes. 他眼睛里闪着坏坏的神色。 2. This wicked fellow needs to be locked up. 需要把这个坏家伙关押起来。 3. The wicked fairy bewitched the prince and turned him into a frog. 邪恶的女妖对王子施魔法，将他变成一只青蛙。 4. It\'s a wicked waste of money. 这样浪费金钱简直是罪恶。 5. The rejection was a wicked blow to her pride. 这一拒绝严重伤害了她的自尊心。 6. Cotton textiles can wick away perspiration. 棉织品可以吸汗。', '副词: wickedly 比较级: wickeder 最高级: wickedest 名词: wickedness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overlap', '[ˌoʊvər\'læp]', 'vt.重叠；重复 vi.有重叠部分 n.重叠部分；重复', '1. A fish\'s scales overlap each other. 鱼鳞是一片片上下交叠起来的。 2. You need to overlap the pieces of wood slightly. 你需要把这些木片搭叠起来。 3. These two papers overlap in content. 这两篇论文有交叉的内容。 4. The programme has been so organized that none of the talks overlap. 日程做了精心安排，以使每一讲都没有重复内容。 5. Channel ranges must not overlap. 频道范围不能重叠。 6. There is a small overlap between the two circles. 在这两个圆周有一小部分重叠。', '过去式: overlapped 过去分词: overlapped 现在分词: overlapping 第三人称单数: overlaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mature', '[mə\'tʃʊr]', 'adj.成熟的；(保单）到期的；考虑周到的 v.成熟；长成', '1. This is the most mature of his plays. 这是他最成熟的一部剧作。 2. She swept her hair back, so she looks more mature than before. 她把头发往后梳，所以显得比以前成熟。 3. Your fixed account is mature and can be withdrawn any time. 您的定期存款已经到期了，随时可以提取。 4. Young as she is, she cares for others and has a mature mind. 她虽然年轻,但却很为他人着想,考虑周到。 5. Girls mature earlier than boys. 女孩比男孩成熟得早些。', '副词: maturely 比较级: maturer 最高级: maturest 名词: matureness 过去式: matured 过去分词: matured 现在分词: maturing 第三人称单数: matures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('marine', '[mə\'riːn]', 'adj.海的；海事的；海生的；航海的 n.海运业；船舶；水兵', '1. His father is a marine biologist. 他父亲是位海洋生物学家。 2. Water pollution imperils all kinds of marine life. 水质污染危及所有海洋生物。 3. He works for the marine court. 他为海事法庭工作。 4. The rocks are covered by marine plants. 岩石被海生植物所覆盖。 5. He sought an officer\'s berth in the merchant marine. 他在商船上找了一个高级船员的职位。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('egg', '[ɛɡ]', 'n.蛋；卵；蛋形物 vt.用蛋覆盖；向 ... 扔蛋 vt.怂恿；煽动', '1. The egg nestled in the long grass. 蛋隐藏在高草中。 2. The black hen lays an egg a day. 那只黑母鸡每天生一个蛋。 3. The tadpole hatches from the egg. 蝌蚪从卵中孵化出来。 4. The egg hatches into a larva (caterpillar). 卵孵化成了幼虫（毛虫）。 5. Egg mayonnaise is made with mayonnaise and hard-boiled eggs. 鸡蛋美乃滋是用蛋黄酱和煮老的鸡蛋做成的。 6. Don\'t let him egg you on--you shouldn\'t take any notice of him. 别听他煽动，你根本就不要去理睬他。', '形容词: eggless 过去式: egged 过去分词: egged 现在分词: egging 第三人称单数: eggs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('back', '[bæk]', 'n.后面；背脊；靠背；后背；后卫 vt.支持；后退 adv.向后地 adj.向后的；后面的；偏远的；过时的；积欠的', '1. Three people can sit in the back of this car. 这车的后座可坐3个人。 2. It encouraged him to talk because his back had stiffened in the night and it hurt truly now. 他靠说话来鼓劲,因为他的背脊在夜里变得僵直,眼下真痛得厉害。 3. You\'ll make your back ache if you carry those heavy buckets. 如果你背那些沉重的桶，你的背会痛的。 4. John plays back in the team. 约翰在这个队打后卫。 5. I\'ll back you up no matter what\'s happening. 不论发生什么事,我都会支持你。 6. Slacken your legs and slowly lie back. 放松双腿, 慢慢向后躺下。 7. The kangaroo uses its back legs to jump. 袋鼠是用牠的后脚在跳。', '形容词: backless 过去式: backed 过去分词: backed 现在分词: backing 第三人称单数: backs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('you', '[jə]', 'pron.你；你们；(泛指)任何人', '1. Do you speak English? 你会说英语吗？ 2. I shall await you at seven-thirty or thereabouts. 我将在7点30分左右等着你。 3. You must all listen carefully. 你们都必须仔细听着。 4. Do you have a room available? 你们有空房间吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('banquet', '[\'bæŋkwɪt]', 'n.宴会 vi.参加宴会 vt.宴请；设宴', '1. The manager was called on to speak at the banquet. 经理应邀在宴会上讲了话。 2. He met the foreign friends and gave a banquet in their honour. 他会见了外国朋友，并设宴招待了他们。 3. The president gave the Prince and his attendants a farewell banquet. 总统为王子和他的随员举行了告别宴会。 4. We gave him a farewell banquet yesterday. 我们昨天为他举行了告别宴会。 5. It\'s interesting for me to banquet. 对我来说参加宴会很有意思。 6. They banqueted her like a queen when she became director of that company. 她成为公司的董事后，他们把她当成女王般设宴款待她。', '名词: banqueter 过去式: banqueted 过去分词: banqueted 现在分词: banqueting 第三人称单数: banquets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('simply', '[\'sɪmpli]', 'adv.简单地；仅仅；简直', '1. Most of these problems won\'t simply dissolve. 大多数这些问题不会简单地解决。 2. Put simply, we accept their offer or go bankrupt. 简单地说吧，我们要么接受他们的条件，要么破产。 3. You may open the tin simply by pulling the puller. 你只要拉这个拉出器，就可以很容易地把罐头打开。 4. Is success simply a matter of working hard? 是否只要勤奋就能成功？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plenty', '[\'plenti]', 'n.丰富；大量；充足 adj.充足的；相当多的 adv.非常；充分', '1. She has plenty of imagination. 她的想象力非常丰富。 2. I padded out my answer with plenty of quotations. 我用了大量引文把答案拉长。 3. You have plenty of time to read. 你有大量的时间读书。 4. A growing child needs plenty of sleep. 正发育的孩子必须睡眠充足。 5. There was plenty water to quench our thirst. 这里有足够的水解渴。 6. There are plenty more fish in the sea. 天涯何处无芳草。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clean', '[kliːn]', 'adj.干净的；纯洁的；完全的；空白的；正当的；精准的 adv.完全地 n.清洁 v.打扫；清扫；擦，刷', '1. You must keep your clothes clean. 你必须保持衣着整洁。 2. I\'ll let you use my bike on condition that you keep it clean. 如果你能保持车子干净,我就让你用我的自行车。 3. Mickey is a clean mouse right from the beginning. 米老鼠从一开始就是一只纯洁的老鼠。 4. President Bush writes a personal letter to Kim, in essence entreating him to come clean on his nuclear program so we can proceed to full normalization. 布什总统给金正日写了一封私人信件，主要是要求他澄清核项目，这样我们可以和他们继续推进完全的正常化关系。 5. I clean forgot about it. 我完全忘记了这件事。 6. The housewife always keeps the sink clean. 主妇总是保持水槽的清洁。 7. Please clean the window as I can hardly see out. 请把窗子弄干净，我几乎看不到外面。', '形容词: cleanable 比较级: cleaner 最高级: cleanest 名词: cleanness 过去式: cleaned 过去分词: cleaned 现在分词: cleaning 第三人称单数: cleans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dark', '[dɑːrk]', 'adj.黑暗的；深色的 n.黑暗；暗处；深色调 v.使变黑；变黑', '1. It\'s a dark and moonless night. 这是一个黑暗无月的夜晚。 2. The baby had dark eyes and dark curls. 那婴孩长着深色的眼睛和深色的鬈发。 3. He ran against a lamp post in the dark. 在黑暗中他撞上了一根电线杆。 4. Reading in the dark is bad for the eyes. 在暗处阅读封眼睛有害。', '形容词: darkish 副词: darkly 比较级: darker 最高级: darkest 名词: darkness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pull', '[pʊl]', 'v.拉；拖；牵；拔；吸引 n.拉；拉力；引力；划船；影响力', '1. The tractor pulls well. 这台拖拉机拉力大。 2. Don\'t pull my hair! 别扯我的头发！ 3. Do not pull the chairs about, boys! 不要把椅子拖来拖去，孩子们！ 4. They call it zugunruhe , the pull of the soul to a far-off place. 人们称之曰迁移兴奋，灵魂被牵往远方。 5. A pull on the rope will make the bell ring. 一拉绳子钟就响。', '名词: puller 过去式: pulled 过去分词: pulled 现在分词: pulling 第三人称单数: pulls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interim', '[\'ɪntərɪm]', 'adj.暂时的；临时的；中间的 n.中间时期；过渡时期；暂定', '1. He worked on an interim basis. 他只是个临时工。 2. Who will lead the interim government? 谁将领导临时政府? 3. They submitted an interim report. 他们递交了一份临时报告。 4. It may turn out to be an interim technology. 这可能只是个过渡技术。 5. What are you doing in the interim? 这期间你在干什么?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('but', '[bət]', 'conj.但是 prep.除 ... 以外 adv.仅仅；只 pron.无不', '1. Our world is but a small part of the cosmos. 我们的世界仅仅是宇宙的一小部分而已。 2. He\'s still but a child. 他仅仅是个小孩子。 3. I want to say nothing but sorry. 我只想说对不起。 4. He can but admit that it was his fault. 他只得承认这是他的错误。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('purify', '[\'pjʊrɪfaɪ]', 'v.(使）净化；（使）精炼；涤罪', '1. The endless lea will purify your thought. 一望无际的草原会净化你的思想。 2. Let\'s purify air with a negative ion generator. 我们用负离子发生器净化一下空气吧。 3. We have forgotten that Water can cleanse,and Fire purify,and that the Earth is mother to us all. 我们已经忘了，水可以洗濯洁净，火可以精炼提纯，大地是每个人的母亲。 4. Hindus purify themselves by bathing in the river Ganges. 印度教徒在恒河中浸泡借以涤罪。', '形容词: purificatory 名词: purifier 过去式: purified 过去分词: purified 现在分词: purifying 第三人称单数: purifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('begin', '[bɪ\'ɡɪn]', 'v.开始；着手', '1. The meeting will begin at nine. 会议将在九点开始。 2. I have to begin with an apology. 我得首先表示歉意。 3. When did you begin learning English? 你何时开始学习英语的？ 4. The leaves begin to fall when autumn comes. 秋天来临时, 树叶开始落下。', '过去式: began 过去分词: begun 现在分词: beginning 第三人称单数: begins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assistance', '[ə\'sɪstəns]', 'n.援助；帮助', '1. We are ready to render them economic assistance. 我们愿意向他们提供经济援助。 2. He gave the assistance to me when I was in trouble. 我有麻烦时,他向我伸出援助之手。 3. You can not rely on his assistance. 你不能指望他能帮助你。 4. I really appreciate your assistance. 衷心感谢您的帮助。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('among', '[ə\'mʌŋ]', 'prep.在 ... 之中；...之一', '1. I live among the mountains. 我住在群山之中。 2. He climbed up the tree and hid among the branches. 他爬上树去,藏在树枝里。 3. New York is among the largest cities in the world. 纽约是世界上最大的几座城市之一。 4. This book counts among the best of his works. 这本书被认为是他的最佳作品之一。', '异体字: amongst');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grieve', '[ɡriːv]', 'vt.使伤心；使悲伤 vi.悲伤；伤心', '1. It grieves me to see him in such bad health. 看见他的健康状况如此不佳，我很伤心。 2. It grieves me to hear how disobedient you\'ve been. 听说你很不听话，使我感到非常难过。 3. She was grieving for the dead baby. 她为死去的孩子悲伤。 4. It\'s no use grieving about past errors. 为过去的错误懊悔不已是无济于事的。', '副词: grievingly 名词: griever 过去式: grieved 过去分词: grieved 现在分词: grieving 第三人称单数: grieves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('junction', '[\'dʒʌŋkʃn]', 'n.连接；会合处；交叉点', '1. The junction was not connected properly. 接口没有正确连接。 2. They decided to effect a junction of two armies. 他们决定两军会师。 3. The map is in error regarding the junction. 这张地图在这个交点上是绘制错了。 4. The gas station is at the junction of two highways 这个加油站位于两条公路的会合处。', '形容词: junctional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('devise', '[dɪ\'vaɪz]', 'vt.设计；发明；遗赠', '1. This time we\'ll devise a better solution. 这次我们将设计一种新的解决方案。 2. The government devised a scheme for redeveloping the city center. 政府制定了市中心重建计划。 3. He devised a new type of transistor. 他发明了一种新的晶体管。', '形容词: devisable 名词: deviser 过去式: devised 过去分词: devised 现在分词: devising 第三人称单数: devises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('threshold', '[\'θreʃhoʊld]', 'n.门槛；开端；界限；入口', '1. The cabin has a flat stone for a threshold. 这间小屋用一条扁平的石头做门槛。 2. The treaty will be the threshold of lasting peace. 这个条约将成为持久和平的开端。 3. He was on the threshold of his career. 他的事业刚刚起步。 4. The tax threshold for a pensioner is $6,000. 领退休金的人的纳税起点是六千美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('float', '[floʊt]', 'v.漂浮；浮现；飘动；提出 n.浮标；漂浮物；漂浮', '1. There is not enough water to float the ship. 没有足够的水使船漂浮起来。 2. These plants float on the surface of the water. 这些植物漂浮在水面上。 3. They float the canoe out into the middle of the river. 他们将独木舟漂浮到河中央。 4. Survival bobbing lets you float for a long time on your stomach. 救生浮游就是让你长时间地仰卧着漂浮在水上。 5. Pay attention to your float! 注意你的浮标！', '形容词: floatable 过去式: floated 过去分词: floated 现在分词: floating 第三人称单数: floats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dilute', '[daɪ\'luːt]', 'vt.稀释；冲淡 adj.冲淡的；稀释的', '1. Dilute the bleach in a gallon of water. 用一加仑水稀释漂白粉。 2. The fragrances are highly diluted. 芳香剂被高度稀释了。 3. The nurse diluted the drug with saline water. 护士用生理盐水把药加以稀释。 4. He thought Rear Admiral Henry\'s presence might dilute the tension of the dinner. 他认为亨利少将的参加也许可以冲淡这顿晚餐的紧张气氛。 5. Readers feel dilute after reading Wei Yingwu\'s poetry, in reality, the poet concealed his solitude under this kind dilute style. 韦应物诗歌给人以冲淡的感觉，其实在这种冲淡的风格下隐含着诗人性格的孤独因素。', '形容词: dilutive 名词: diluter 过去式: diluted 过去分词: diluted 现在分词: diluting 第三人称单数: dilutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('boost', '[buːst]', 'v.提高；增加；鼓励；举起；为...做宣传 n.增加；推进；鼓励', '1. This new technique will boost food production. 这种新工艺将会提高食品产量。 2. The publication of this book boost my confidence. 这本书的出版增强了我的信心。 3. The change of management has boosted morale throughout the company. 管理层的变更使整个公司士气大振。 4. Boost me up the tree and I\'ll get the apple. 把我托上树,我就能摘到那只苹果了。 5. Last month saw a tremendous boost in sales. 上个月的销售额激增。', '过去式: boosted 过去分词: boosted 现在分词: boosting 第三人称单数: boosts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('similar', '[\'sɪmələr]', 'adj.类似的', '1. The two buildings are similar on the whole. 从整体来看，这两幢楼是相似的。 2. I sympathize with you; I\'ve had a similar unhappy experience myself. 我很同情你，我自己也有过类似的不幸遭遇。 3. He talked about it in a similar way. 他对此事有相似的说法。 4. Gold is similar in color to brass. 金和铜颜色相仿。', '副词: similarly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rest', '[rest]', 'n.剩余的部分；休息；支撑物；休止符 v.休息；(使)倚靠；使(视线)停留在；搁在；依赖；基于；搁置；埋葬', '1. We\'ll eat some of the bread and keep the rest for breakfast. 我们将吃一点面包，剩下的留到早饭时吃。 2. You look tired. You need a good rest. 你看来累了。你需要好好休息一下。 3. A rest shall be placed at the end of a row of books to keep them upright. 一排书的末端应放个支撑物以使书本保持直立。 4. When the song came to a rest, she paused for a while. 唱到了休止符的时候，她停顿了一下。 5. It would be nice to sit down and rest for a while. 坐下来休息一会儿是很好的。', '名词: rester 过去式: rested 过去分词: rested 现在分词: resting 第三人称单数: rests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('doctor', '[\'dɑːktər]', 'n.博士；医生 v.篡改，伪造；阉割', '1. He is a Doctor of Philosophy. 他是一位哲学博士。 2. His illness was more serious than the doctor first thought. 他的病较医生原来以为的更严重。 3. How else can the doctor save him? 医院还有别的方法可以救他吗？', '形容词: doctoral 过去式: doctored 过去分词: doctored 现在分词: doctoring 第三人称单数: doctors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('student', '[\'stuːdnt]', 'n.学生；学者', '1. A student should always be curious to learn. 学生应该始终具有强烈的求知欲。 2. A young student fainted in the hot sun. 有个年幼的学生在炎炎烈日下晕倒了。 3. John is more diligent than any other student in his class. 约翰比班上其他的同学用功。 4. Such a good student as he (is) will succeed. 像他这样的好学生一定会成功。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clever', '[\'klevər]', 'adj.聪明的；灵巧的', '1. It\'s a clever speech, but there was no real meat in it. 这演说很动听，可是没什么内容。 2. He\'s so clever, he makes me feel inferior. 他那么聪明，让我自愧不如。 3. Mr. Jones is a clever carpenter. 琼斯先生是个巧木匠。 4. He is clever at arithmetic. 他擅长算术。', '副词: cleverly 比较级: cleverer 最高级: cleverest 名词: cleverness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hoist', '[hɔɪst]', 'v.升起；升高；举起 n.起重机；升高', '1. They hoist cargo with a locomobile crane. 他们用自动推进的起重机吊起货物。', '名词: hoister 过去式: hoisted 过去分词: hoisted 现在分词: hoisting 第三人称单数: hoists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('breed', '[briːd]', 'v.繁殖；养育；引起，产生；教养 n.品种；血统', '1. Wild animals don\'t breed well in captivity. 野生动物圈养时不好繁殖。 2. How often do lions breed? 狮子多长时间产一次仔? 3. I breed some chicks for pets. 我养了一些小鸡当宠物。 4. Spartan youths were bred as warriors. 斯巴达青年被培养成战士. 5. Spaniel is a breed of dog with large ears. 西班牙猎狗是一种长着大耳朵的猎狗。', '过去式: bred 过去分词: bred 现在分词: breeding 第三人称单数: breeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exclaim', '[ɪk\'skleɪm]', 'v.大叫；呼喊；大声说出', '1. The children exclaimed with excitement. 孩子们兴奋地大叫。 2. \"How beautiful the lake is!\" we exclaimed. 我们叫喊着说,\"这个湖多美啊!\" 3. She exclaimed at the beautiful view. 她对这美丽的景色感到惊奇。 4. She exclaimed that she was innocent. 她大声呼喊她是无辜的。', '名词: exclaimer 过去式: exclaimed 过去分词: exclaimed 现在分词: exclaiming 第三人称单数: exclaims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assert', '[ə\'sɜːrt]', 'vt.断言；主张，坚持；生效；维护', '1. She asserted that he was innocent. 她断言，他是无罪的。 2. Upon inspection, we assert that the systems development process is empirical 通过以上分析,我们断言系统开发过程是经验的 3. We encouraged him to assert his view of the matter. 我们鼓励他坚持自己对此事的看法。 4. The laws of historical development will assert themselves. 历史发展的规律是不可抗拒的。', '形容词: assertable 名词: asserter 过去式: asserted 过去分词: asserted 现在分词: asserting 第三人称单数: asserts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remark', '[rɪ\'mɑːrk]', 'n.评论；备注；注意 v.评论；注意到', '1. They made rude remarks about her appearance. 他们对她的外表横加粗暴的评论。 2. The teacher asked the students to make a remark on this page. 老师要求学生在这页备注。 3. Ellen later regretted her remarks about his private affairs. 后来,艾伦后悔的发现没有好好注意他的私事。 4. The editor remarked that article was well written. 编者评论说那篇文章写得很好。', '名词: remarker 过去式: remarked 过去分词: remarked 现在分词: remarking 第三人称单数: remarks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ground', '[ɡraʊnd]', 'n.地面；地方；根据；主题；立场；水平；背景 v.使停飞；困在家中；放在地上；使 ... 搁浅；打基础 动词grind的过去式和过去分词形式', '1. You shouldn\'t sit on the ground when it\'s wet. 地面潮湿时就不应该坐在地上。 2. The expedition covered a lot of ground. 探险队到过很多地方。 3. Boredom is not a ground for divorce. 日久生厌不能成为离婚的理由。 4. There is no point in going over the same ground twice. 把同样的主题重温两遍根本就没有什么意义。 5. All aircrafts at London Airport were grounded by fog today. 因大雾天气,今天伦敦机场的所有飞机都被迫停飞。', '过去式: grounded 过去分词: grounded 现在分词: grounding 第三人称单数: grounds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fetch', '[fetʃ]', 'vt.取来；卖得；给（某人）一击 n.取得', '1. Fetch me the tape from my drawer. 请把我抽屉里的磁带取来。 2. Shall I fetch your coat for you? 我去把上衣给你取来好吗? 3. This house should fetch a good price. 这所房子应该卖个好价钱。 4. The picture should fetch 2000 pounds at auction. 这张画拍卖可得2000英镑。 5. Hence, the system needs to fetch the needed data as soon as possible.The existing way is based on file prefetching. 因此若要降低使用者等待时间，则需加快反应时间，必须尽早取得档案资料。', '名词: fetcher 过去式: fetched 过去分词: fetched 现在分词: fetching 第三人称单数: fetches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('painting', '[\'peɪntɪŋ]', 'n.画，油画；绘画 动词paint的现在分词.', '1. The painting took his fancy, so he bought it. 这幅画被他看中了,所以他就把它买了下来。 2. Looking at a beautiful painting always gives one satisfaction. 观赏一幅美丽的图画使人心满意足。 3. There are three paintings on the wall. 墙上有三幅画。 4. That is an oil painting of a landscape in spring. 那是一幅描绘春天景色的油画。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('zinc', '[zɪŋk]', 'n. 锌 vt. 在 ... 上镀锌', '1. The fusion of copper and zinc make the metal brass. 铜和锌的熔化制成黄铜。 2. Zinc is generally caustic to foliage. 锌常对幼叶有腐蚀作用。', '简写符号: Zn 过去式: zinced/zincked 过去分词: zinced/zincked 现在分词: zincing/zincking 第三人称单数: zincs/zincks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hall', '[hɔːl]', 'n.大厅；礼堂', '1. The lecture is to be delivered at the hall. 演讲将在大厅进行。 2. There was a low murmur of conversation in the hall. 大厅里有窃窃私语声。 3. A multitude of people gathered at the gate of the exhibition hall. 大群人聚集在展览大厅的门口。 4. There were plenty of people in front of the town\'s Hall. 在城镇的大礼堂前有许多人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('capital', '[\'kæpɪtl]', 'n.首都；资本；大写字母；[建筑]柱顶 adj.资本的；大写的；一流的；首要的；极其严重的；涉及死亡的', '1. Beijing is the capital of China. 北京是中国的首都。 2. All the government offices are in the capital. 所有的政府机关都在首都。 3. The main impediment to growth is a lack of capital. 影响发展的主要障碍是缺乏资本。 4. In this essay, some punctuations and capitals have been left out. 在这篇文章里,一些标点和大写字母已经不在了。 5. Capital and output ratios, especially in those industries which imports technologies, tend to decline. 资本与产出的比率,尤其是在引进技术的企业中呈下降趋势!', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bill', '[bɪl]', 'n.帐单；钞票；清单；议案；海报；节目单；锚钩；鸟喙；帽舌 v.开帐单；把 ... 列成表；用海报宣传；(鸟嘴)接触；爱抚 Bill n.比尔(男子名)', '1. A 10% service charge is added on to the bill. 帐单上包括了百分之十的服务费。 2. I have a 5-dollar bill. 我有一张5美元的钞票。 3. A bill came along with the package. 清单与包裹一并到达。 4. After a long debate the bill was passed. 经长时间的辩论，议案获得通过。 5. We\'ll bill you next week for your purchases. 下周我们将把你购买的物品开账单给你。 6. Bill Gates is an American citizen. 比尔·盖茨是美国公民。', '形容词: billable 过去式: billed 过去分词: billed 现在分词: billing 第三人称单数: bills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('maintenance', '[\'meɪntənəns]', 'n.维修；维护；保持；生活费用；抚养费', '1. He\'s taking classes in car maintenance. 他正在上汽车维修课。 2. The machinery requires constant maintenance. 这些机器需要经常保养维修。 3. The roof of the ancient temple caved in because of bad maintenance. 那座古老的宙宇由于维护不好屋顶塌了下来。 4. Our policy is maintenance of friendly relations with all countries. 我们的政策是与所有国家保持友好关系。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('carriage', '[\'kærɪdʒ]', 'n.四轮马车；客车车厢；运输；运费；举止；托架', '1. The carriage passed through the palace gate. 马车进入了宫殿的大门。 2. The carriage that he had ordered duly arrived, and we drove off. 他叫的马车按时到，我们就坐上去走了。 3. I\'ll be sitting in the 3rd carriage from the front of the train. 我将坐在第三节车厢。 4. Contract at his own expense for the carriage and insurance of the goods from the named port of shipment. 自付费用订立从指定的装运港运输货物的合同和保险合同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('proposition', '[ˌprɑːpə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.提议；事业；命题 vt.向 ... 调情', '1. His proposition is good in theory but cannot be put into practice. 他的建议在理论上可以，但不能付诸实现。 2. This is the inverse of his earlier proposition. 这和他早些时候提的建议截然相反。 3. This is not money-making proposition. 这不是个赚钱的事业。 4. Tunnelling under the English Channel is a big proposition. 在英吉利海峡海底凿隧道是一个大问题。 5. She was propositioned several times in the course of the evening. 整个晚上有人几次向她提出非分要求。', '形容词: propositional 副词: propositionally 过去式: propositioned 过去分词: propositioned 现在分词: propositioning 第三人称单数: propositions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('otherwise', '[\'ʌðərwaɪz]', 'adv.否则；不同地；在不同方面 adj.不同的', '1. Seize the chance, otherwise you\'ll regret it. 抓住这个机会，否则你会后悔的。 2. He should have been working, but he was otherwise engaged. 他应该在工作,可他却干别的事。 3. She is not very clever, but otherwise she\'s a nice girl. 她并不聪明，但在其他方面，她倒是个好姑娘。 4. The truth is quite otherwise. 实情大有出入。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('son', '[sʌn]', 'n.儿子；孩子（长者对后辈的称呼）', '1. His wife born him a son. 他妻子给他生了一个儿子。 2. My little son is fond of playing practical jokes on me. 我的小儿子喜欢对我玩恶作剧。 3. I haven\'t heard any news from my son lately. 我最近没听到我儿子的任何音讯。 4. America owes you a debt of gratitude, son. 美国深深地感谢你,孩子。', '形容词: sonly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('establishment', '[ɪ\'stæblɪʃmənt]', 'n.确立；建立；家业；机构；当局', '1. Because of the establishment of the patriarchy, androgyny gradually retreated from the mainstream society. 但由于父权制度的确立，“双性同体”思想逐渐从主流文化中隐退。 2. British colonialism led to the establishment of a large empire. 英国的殖民主义成就了幅员辽阔的大英帝国。 3. He keeps a large establishment. 他拥有巨大家业。 4. A zoo is a very costly establishment. 动物园是一个花费极大的机构。', '动词: establish');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compassion', '[kəm\'pæʃn]', 'n.怜悯；同情', '1. I had compassion for him. 我怜悯他。 2. He teaches us to have compassion on the poor. 他教导我们对穷人应有怜悯心。 3. Compassion is a sign of weakness. 怜悯是弱者的标志。 4. I should not have compassion for those lofty birds. 我不会怜悯这些高贵的鸟。', '形容词: compassionless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exit', '[\'eksɪt]', 'n.出口；退场 v.离去；退出', '1. She made a dart for the exit. 她冲向出口。 2. At the roundabout, take the third exit. 在环状交叉路口，从第三条出路驶出。 3. I was eventually granted an exit visa. 我终于获得了出境签证。 4. He made a quick exit to avoid meeting her. 他迅速离去以避免见到她。', '过去式: exited 过去分词: exited 现在分词: exiting 第三人称单数: exits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('design', '[dɪ\'zaɪn]', 'n.设计；图样；图案；目的 v.设计；计划', '1. This dress is of the latest design. 这件衣服是最新设计。 2. He chalked out a design on the blackboard. 他用粉笔在黑板上勾划出一个图样。 3. The bedcover was quilted in a flower design. 床罩被缝成花卉图案。 4. His evil designs were frustrated. 他的罪恶企图未能得逞。 5. He designed us a beautiful house. 他为我们设计了一所很美的房子。', '形容词: designable 过去式: designed 过去分词: designed 现在分词: designing 第三人称单数: designs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attract', '[ə\'trækt]', 'v.吸引；引来', '1. The flower show attracted large crowds this year. 今年的花展吸引了大批观众。 2. She gave a quiet cough to attract my attention. 她轻轻地咳了一声好引起我注意。 3. His comments were bound to attract criticism. 他的评论必然会招致批评。', '形容词: attractable 名词: attracter 过去式: attracted 过去分词: attracted 现在分词: attracting 第三人称单数: attracts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('perfect', '[\'pɜːrfɪkt]', 'adj.完美的；完全的；完满的；十足的；理想的 vt.使完美；使完全', '1. Laurel was a perfect girl in every way. 从各方面讲，罗拉都是一个完美的女孩。 2. No one expects you to be perfect, but we do expect you to do your best always. 没人指望你完美无缺，但是我们盼望你永远尽最大的努力。 3. One day being perfect health is much. 获得一天完全的健康也不算少。 4. I insist on perfect sobriety and silence. 我坚决要求完全的肃静。 5. She went to France to perfect her French. 她为了学好法语去过法国。', '名词: perfecter 过去式: perfected 过去分词: perfected 现在分词: perfecting 第三人称单数: perfects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('opaque', '[oʊ\'peɪk]', 'adj.不透明的；难懂的', '1. This is an opaque cup. 这是一个不透明的杯子。 2. The window is made of opaque glass. 这扇窗是用不透明的玻璃做的。 3. The report was written in long, opaque sentences. 报告中的句子又长又难懂。 4. Their intentions remained opaque. 他们的意图仍然令人费解。', '副词: opaquely 名词: opaqueness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reduce', '[rɪ\'duːs]', 'v.减少；缩小；使落魄；简化；还原', '1. The new government\'s prime task is to reduce the level of inflation. 新政府的主要任务是减低通货膨胀的水平。 2. We need to reduce our dependence on oil as a source of energy. 在能源方面,我们需减少对石油的依赖。 3. We must gradually reduce the wage gap. 我们要逐步缩小工资差距。 4. They were reduced to begging. 他们沦落到得要饭。', '形容词: reducible 副词: reducibly 名词: reducer 过去式: reduced 过去分词: reduced 现在分词: reducing 第三人称单数: reduces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('around', '[ə\'raʊnd]', 'prep.到处；在 ... 附近；围绕；大约；符合 adv.到处；在周围；现有；闲散地；转弯；掉头 adj.存在的；在风行的', '1. He runs around the playground. 他在运动场上到处跑。 2. I saw him around the place this morning. 今天早上我看见他就在那儿附近。 3. The earth moves around the sun. 地球围绕太阳运动。 4. There\'re around 1000 employees in this company. 这个公司大约有1000名员工。 5. We have travelled around in Europe for six weeks. 我们在欧洲各地旅行了六个星期。 6. He is the most intelligent artist around today. 他是如今在世的最有才华的艺术家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('meditation', '[ˌmedɪ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.沉思；冥想', '1. He is deep in meditation. 他陷入沉思中。 2. Meditation is a form of guided thought. 沉思是一种引导思维的形式。 3. She found peace through yoga and meditation. 她通过瑜伽和冥想找到了宁静。', '形容词: meditational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nurse', '[nɜːrs]', 'n.护士；保姆 v.看护；护理；栽培', '1. A nurse came to put on a clean dressing for him. 一位护士来给他包上干净的绷带。 2. The nurse diluted the drug with saline water. 护士用生理盐水把药加以稀释。 3. The nurse is preparing the child to go to hospital. 保姆正在为孩子住院作准备。 4. We\'ll have to put the baby to nurse. 我们只能请人照看婴孩。', '名词: nurser 过去式: nursed 过去分词: nursed 现在分词: nursing 第三人称单数: nurses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lorry', '[\'lɔːri]', 'n.卡车', '1. Bind down the ropes around the load on the lorry. 把绕在卡车上货物外面的绳子扎紧。 2. A heavy lorry floundered about in deep snow. 一辆重型卡车在厚厚的积雪中艰难地行进。', '名词复数: lorries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diplomatic', '[ˌdɪplə\'mætɪk]', 'adj.外交的；古字体的；老练的', '1. He has diplomatic immunity. 他有外交豁免权。 2. The exercise of patience is essential in diplomatic negotiations. 在外交谈判中，重要的是要有耐性。 3. He tried to be diplomatic when he refused their invitation. 他在拒绝他们的邀请时，尽可能地婉转些。 4. John was as diplomatic as Mary when talking to the press. 约翰在与媒体打交道时和玛丽一样老练。', '副词: diplomatically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('volunteer', '[ˌvɑːlən\'tɪr]', 'n.志愿者；(自行生长的)植物 v.(自愿)做', '1. He enlisted as a volunteer in the army. 他以志愿兵从军。 2. He works as a volunteer at off time. 在业余时间 3. He volunteered a statement to the police. 他自动向警方供出情况。 4. Many people volunteer to work on the farms. 许多人自动到农场劳动。', '过去式: volunteered 过去分词: volunteered 现在分词: volunteering 第三人称单数: volunteers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('psychiatry', '[saɪ\'kaɪətri]', 'n.精神病学', '1. Psychiatry has the character of transdiscipline. 精神病学具有跨学科性质。 2. Psychiatry is the area of medicine that treats mental and emotional conditions. 精神病学是对待心理和情绪条件的医学领域。', '形容词: psychiatric 副词: psychiatrically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('latitude', '[\'lætɪtuːd]', 'n.纬度；自由', '1. The latitude of the island is 30 degrees north. 这个岛的纬度是北纬三十度。 2. Latitude reaches a maximum of 90°at the poles. 两极纬度的最大值为90°。 3. You have a wide latitude to act as you think best. 你拥有自己认为最好的、广泛的行动上的自由。 4. We allow considerable latitude at these hearings. 我们在这种听证会上允许相当大的自由。', '形容词: latitudinal 副词: latitudinally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('champagne', '[ʃæm\'peɪn]', 'n.香槟酒；香槟色', '1. The champagne was quaffed from huge golden goblets. 香槟酒被从金色的高脚杯里一饮而尽。 2. Champagne is full of bubbles. 香槟酒有很多气泡。 3. The champagne cork popped when he pulled it out. 他拔香槟酒的瓶塞时它砰的一声开了。 4. He was drinking cheap champagne with a raffish air. 他喝著廉价的香槟酒，样子十分放荡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cafe', '[kæ\'feɪ]', 'n.咖啡馆；小餐馆', '1. This cafe keeps late into the night. 这家咖啡馆一直开到深夜。 2. The uproar in the cafe lasted long after midnight. 咖啡馆的喧闹一直持续到午夜之后很久。 3. The police came and ejected the noisy youths from the cafe room. 警察来了,把那些吵吵嚷嚷的青年人从咖啡馆里撵了出去。 4. This cafe is a rendezvous for writers and artists. 这家小餐馆是作家和艺术家经常聚会的地方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pressure', '[\'preʃər]', 'n.压强；压力；压迫 v.施压', '1. My father suffers from high blood pressure. 我父亲有高血压。 2. The pressure of work was too great for him. 工作的压力使他承受不了。 3. He works well under pressure. 他在有压力的情况下工作很出色。 4. The tooth became sore to pressure and there is a dull gnawing pain. 该齿对于压迫作痛，且有钝麻如咬的疼痛。 5. Now you are trying to pressure me. 你现在试图向我施压。', '过去式: pressured 过去分词: pressured 现在分词: pressuring 第三人称单数: pressures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('street', '[striːt]', 'n.街道；马路 adj.街道的', '1. I met him in the street. 我在街上遇到他。 2. He stood in a strange street. 他站在一条陌生的街道上。 3. This street is four times shorter than that one. 这条街道比那条短四倍。 4. The troops walked in procession through the street. 军队排成队伍走过街道。 5. I like to buy a street map of the city. 我想买一张这个城市的街道地图。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mineral', '[\'mɪnərəl]', 'n.矿物(石）；矿物质', '1. Coal is a mineral. 煤是一种矿物。 2. We are digging for mineral deposits. 我们正在掘地探矿。 3. This shop sells mineral water. 这家商店卖矿泉水。 4. They have sold up ten crates of mineral water in the afternoon. 他们这个下午卖掉了十箱矿泉水。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spacious', '[\'speɪʃəs]', 'adj.宽敞的；广阔的', '1. The hotel is neither spacious nor comfortable. 这旅馆既不宽敞也不舒服。 2. The systematic arrangement of chairs makes the hall look spacious. 座椅按照顺序排列，这使得礼堂里显得很宽敞。 3. In its spacious halls are displayed over8000 priceless relics. 在它宽敞的大厅里，展出了8000多件珍贵文物。 4. The museum is complemented by a spacious garden. 广大宽阔的庭院为博物馆增色不少。', '副词: spaciously 名词: spaciousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('betray', '[bɪ\'treɪ]', 'vt.背叛；出卖；泄露；显露', '1. He betrayed his country. 他背叛了他的国家。 2. He promised never to betray the organization. 他发誓永不背叛组织。 3. He was seduced to betray his friend. 他受唆使而出卖朋友。 4. As long as you don\'t betray me, I\'ll do whatever you ask me to. 只要你不出卖我,要我做什么我都愿意。', '名词: betrayal 过去式: betrayed 过去分词: betrayed 现在分词: betraying 第三人称单数: betrays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conduct', '[kən\'dʌkt]', 'n.行为；举动；品行 v.引导；指挥；管理 vt.导电；传热', '1. Your conduct is not consistent with what you say. 你的言行不一致。 2. His behavior transgressed the unwritten rules of social conduct. 他的行为违反了不成文的社交规范。 3. His conduct roused the suspicion of the police. 他的举动引起了警察的怀疑。 4. He has good conduct. 他品行端正。 5. The guide conducted us around the ruins of the ancient city. 导游引导我们游览了古城废墟。 6. Most metals can conduct electricity. 大多数金属能导电。', '形容词: conductible 名词: conductibility 过去式: conducted 过去分词: conducted 现在分词: conducting 第三人称单数: conducts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trivial', '[\'trɪviəl]', 'adj.不重要的；琐碎的', '1. It\'s a trivial matter and not worth fighting about. 区区小事不值得争吵。 2. He could remember every trivial incident in great detail. 他能把每件小事的细节都记得很清楚。 3. I object to being jumped upon for trivial matter like this. 我讨厌因这种小事而受人责备。 4. Don\'t be angry over such trivial matters. 别为这些琐事生气。', '副词: trivially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appointment', '[ə\'pɔɪntmənt]', 'n.约会；任命；设备；职位', '1. I\'ve made an appointment for a facial next week. 我已经预约了下周去美容。 2. He wants to change his appointment from Monday to Wednesday. 他想把他的约会从星期一改到星期三。 3. His promotion to manager was a popular appointment. 他升任经理是众望所归的。 4. The appointments in this hotel are very good. 这旅馆的设备很好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seat', '[siːt]', 'n.座位；底座；席位；臀部；所在地 vt.使坐下；可容纳 vi.坐', '1. He sat down on the nearest available seat. 他在最近的空座位上坐下来。 2. She got on the bus and picked a seat up front. 她上了公车,找了个最前面的座位。 3. His body was flung across the cell and fetched up against the base of the lavatory seat. 他的身体倒到牢房另一头去，掉在便盆的底座前。 4. He lost his seat in the Parliament at the election. 他在选举中失去了议会中的席位。 5. We want to buy a car that can seat five persons. 我们想要买一辆能坐五个人的汽车。 6. She purposely sat in the outside seat. 她故意坐在外面座位上。', '过去式: seated 过去分词: seated 现在分词: seating 第三人称单数: seats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('infect', '[ɪn\'fekt]', 'vt.传染；感染', '1. The open wound soon became infected. 裸露的伤口很快就受到了感染。 2. The flu virus infected almost the entire class. 全班几乎人人都染上了流行性感冒病毒。 3. There is a virus that infects word-processing documents recently. 最近有种病毒专门传染WORD文件。 4. Her cheerful spirits and bubble laughter infect the whole class. 她那快乐的情绪和爽朗的笑声感染了全班。', '过去式: infected 过去分词: infected 现在分词: infecting 第三人称单数: infects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pool', '[puːl]', 'n.水塘；游泳池 n.共同储金；联营；美式撞球 v.共用；汇集', '1. A fringe of trees stood round the pool. 池塘四周耸立着一圈树木。 2. They stripped off and jumped into the pool. 他们脱掉衣服，跳进了池子。 3. There is a swimming pool in the park. 公园里有一个游泳池。 4. To save gas, many people joined the car pool. 为节省汽油,许多人参加车辆共乘。 5. Let\' s pool our money to buy a car. 让我们合资来买一辆汽车。', '名词: pooler 过去式: pooled 过去分词: pooled 现在分词: pooling 第三人称单数: pools');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('throne', '[θroʊn]', 'n.王位；君主', '1. Henry IV usurped the throne of England. 亨利四世篡夺了英国的王位。 2. He set up a claim to the throne. 他自称王位是属于他的。 3. He was only eight when he ascended the throne. 他登上王位时才八岁。 4. He swore allegiance to the throne. 他宣誓效忠国王。', '过去式: throned 过去分词: throned 现在分词: throning 第三人称单数: thrones');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surge', '[sɜːrdʒ]', 'n.汹涌；波涛；猛增 v.汹涌；涌起；激增；[海]缆绳滑脱', '1. A surge of demonstrators broke through the fence. 汹涌而来的示威者冲破了围栏。 2. The great surge had built up in the Gulf Stream. 汹涌的巨浪在墨西哥湾流形成了。 3. Oil was the prime cause of the price surge. 石油是物价上涨的主要原因。 4. The tides surged over the rocks. 潮水奔腾着涌过礁石。', '过去式: surged 过去分词: surged 现在分词: surging 第三人称单数: surges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mean', '[miːn]', 'v.意思是；打算；导致；意味 adj.低劣的；刻薄的；卑鄙的；出色的；吝啬的；平均的；中等的 n.平均值；平均数；中间；中庸', '1. What does this word mean? 这个单词是什么意思？ 2. I mean that\'s his own decision to resign or not. 我的意思是说辞不辞职是他自己的决定。 3. I mean to call on you tomorrow. 我打算明天看望你。 4. His father meant him to be an engineer. 他父亲打算让他当工程师。 5. Don\'t be so mean to your little brother! 别对你弟弟那麽刻薄！ 6. It is an estimate of the mean of the population. 这是对人口平均数的一个估计。', '副词: meanly 比较级: meaner 最高级: meanest 过去式: meant 过去分词: meant 现在分词: meaning 第三人称单数: means');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mercury', '[\'mɜːrkjəri]', 'n.水银；（M~）水星；精神', '1. Mercury is a fluid substance. 水银是流体状之。 2. Mercury weighs more than water by about 14 times. 水银比水重约十三倍。 3. Mercury is too dry and poor in oxygen. 水星上面过于干燥，并且缺乏氧气。 4. He has no mercury in him. 他没有精神。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('artery', '[\'ɑːrtəri]', 'n.动脉；干线', '1. Blood was spouting from the severed artery . 血从切断的动脉里喷出来。 2. This widens the inside of the artery, restoring blood flow. 这样会扩展动脉的内腔，达到恢复血流的效果。 3. The Yangtse River is one of the main arteries of traffic in China. 长江是中国的交通要道之一。 4. This is the place where the three main arteries of West London traffic meet. 这是伦敦西区三条主要干线会合的地方。', '名词复数: arteries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commonwealth', '[\'kɑːmənwelθ]', 'n.联合体；联邦', '1. The three republics have decided to forma a commonwealth of independent states. 这三个共和国家决定组成一个独立国家联合体。 2. He is the chairman of the commonwealth of artists. 他是艺术家协会的主席。 3. Puerto Rico remains a US commonwealth, not a state. 波多黎各至今仍然是美国的一个自治政区，而不是一个州。 4. Dominion is a part of the British Commonwealth. 自治领是英联邦的一个组成部分。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('error', '[\'erər]', 'n.错误；过失；误差；谬误', '1. He overlooked a spelling error on the first page. 他没有看出第一页中有个拼写错误。 2. An alert listener will have noticed the error. 耳朵尖的人能听出这个错。 3. Every man is liable to error. 人人都可能犯错误。 4. The accident was caused by human error. 这宗事故是人为过失造成的。', '形容词: errorless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fat', '[fæt]', 'adj.肥胖的；多脂肪的；丰满的 n.脂肪；肥肉 vt.使变胖', '1. If you don\'t get more exercise, you\'ll get fat. 如果你不多作运动，就会发胖。 2. The tight jumper only accentuated his fat stomach. 那件紧身套头毛衣反更突出了他那肥胖的肚子。 3. I was so tightly wedged between two fat women that it was difficult for me to get up and leave the bus. 我被两个肥胖的女人紧紧地挤在中间，以致于要站起来下公共汽车都很难。 4. Are there any other fruits that are rich in fat? 还有什么水果含大量脂肪? 5. You can drink water without getting fat. 喝水是不会使你变胖的。', '副词: fatly 比较级: fatter 最高级: fattest 名词: fatness 过去式: fatted 过去分词: fatted 现在分词: fatting 第三人称单数: fats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('these', '[ðiːz]', 'pron.这些 adj.这些的', '1. These are my books. 这些是我的书。 2. I\'m just going to check in these books at the library. 我要去图书馆还这些书。 3. We have been working hard these days. 这些天来，我们一直在努力工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('steep', '[stiːp]', 'adj.险峻的；陡峭的；急剧的、大起大落的 v.浸泡，浸透，湿透；沉浸，笼罩', '1. This hill is too steep to ride up on a bicycle. 这山太陡了，骑自行车可上不去。 2. The last part of the ascent is very steep. 最后一段上坡路很陡。 3. The bus toiled up the steep hill. 公共汽车艰难地爬上陡峭的山岗。 4. It’s priced at fifty pounds, and I think that’s a bit steep for a secondhand lawn mower. 那东西标价50英镑，而我认为对于一部二手货的割草机来说，那个价钱不合理。', '副词: steeply 比较级: steeper 最高级: steepest 名词: steepness 过去式: steeped 过去分词: steeped 现在分词: steeping 第三人称单数: steeps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gramme', '[\'ɡræm]', 'n.<英>克(重量单位) =gram(美)', '1. Output: to gramme degree for one labour and one day. 生产：人均日产可达克级，药用量是微克级。 2. Phil Gramm was a general in that conflict, and there was nothing cute about it. 菲尔.;格兰姆就是这场战争的总指挥！这绝不是什么好玩的事情！ 3. This pro - gramme is my brain child and I strongly object to somebody taking over the production of it. 这个计划是我想出来的杰作，我强烈反对他盗用。 4. Cost: material costs 10 yuan, water and electricity costs 1 yuan and laborage costs 15 yuan for each gramme output. 成本：按每克计算，所需原料成本10元，水电1元，工资15元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pond', '[pɑːnd]', 'n.池塘', '1. There are some reeds in the pond. 池塘里有些芦苇。 2. The deer lowered its head to drink from the pond. 鹿低下头去喝池塘里的水。 3. The farm has a pond from which the cattle can drink. 农场有一个供牛饮水的池塘。 4. The cattle had trodden a path to the pond. 牛群踩出了一条通往池塘的小径。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spirit', '[\'spɪrɪt]', 'n.精神；心灵；幽灵；精灵 (复)spirits：精力；情绪；烈酒. v.使精神振作；偷偷带走', '1. He is endued with a spirit of public service. 他富有为公众服务的精神。 2. We need a spirit of enterprise if we are to overcome our difficulties. 如果我们要克服困难，我们就要有进取精神。 3. Now the rat of Panic was gnawing at Byron\'s spirit. 如今恐慌正象耗子一样在啃啮拜伦的心灵。 4. Music lifted up the listening spirit. 音乐净化升华了倾听它的心灵。 5. The boss is being in royal spirits right now. 此刻，老板情绪极好。', '过去式: spirited 过去分词: spirited 现在分词: spiriting 第三人称单数: spirits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('empty', '[\'empti]', 'adj.空的；空洞的；空虚的；空腹的 v.倒空；变空；排空 n.空物', '1. His room is empty. 他的房间是空的。 2. His wordy and empty speech was a frost. 他的冗长空洞的讲话使人厌烦。 3. He didn\'t want to retire and lead an empty life. 他不想退休过空虚的生活。 4. This medicine must be taken on an empty stomach. 这种药必须空腹服用。 5. They emptied the biscuits onto the plate. 他们把饼干倒在盘子里。 6. Empties are not taken back. 不退瓶子。', '副词: emptily 比较级: emptier 最高级: emptiest 名词: emptiness 名词复数: empties 过去式: emptied 过去分词: emptied 现在分词: emptying 第三人称单数: empties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cultivate', '[\'kʌltɪveɪt]', 'vt.栽培；耕作；培养；陶冶；结交(朋友)', '1. He was granted many privileges to cultivate crops. 他被给予许多特权来培育农作物。 2. They moved to the country to cultivate the soil . 他们搬到乡下去种地。 3. The people cultivate mainly rice and beans. 这里的人们主要种植稻子和豆类。 4. Father tries to cultivate my love for art. 父亲企图培养我对艺术的爱好。', '形容词: cultivatable 过去式: cultivated 过去分词: cultivated 现在分词: cultivating 第三人称单数: cultivates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sort', '[sɔːrt]', 'n.种类；某一种人 v.整理；分类；处理；安排妥当', '1. What sort of book do you want? 你要哪一类的书？ 2. This sort of wet weather plays hell with my chest. 这种潮湿天气对我的肺有害。 3. He is a good sort (of a fellow). 他是个好样儿的。 4. My brother would never cheat on his wife; he\'s not that sort. 我哥哥永远不会背着妻子在外面拈花惹草；他不是那种人。 5. We must sort out the good apples from the bad ones. 我们必须把好的苹果与坏的分开。', '形容词: sortable 名词: sorter 过去式: sorted 过去分词: sorted 现在分词: sorting 第三人称单数: sorts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whistle', '[\'wɪsl]', 'n.口哨；汽笛；警笛 v.吹口哨；鸣汽笛；呼啸；吹口哨召唤', '1. The whistle goes at the end of the match. 比赛结束时哨声响了。 2. He gave a loud whistle of gladness. 他吹了一声响亮的口号表示高兴。 3. The whistle went and the man knocked off for lunch. 汽笛响了，工人们停工午餐。 4. The horse shied at the shrill whistle. 那匹马听到刺耳的汽笛声，惊得往后倒退。 5. The little boy rounded his lips to whistle. 那个小男孩把双唇收圆好吹口哨。', '过去式: whistled 过去分词: whistled 现在分词: whistling 第三人称单数: whistles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mate', '[meɪt]', 'n.配偶；伙伴；同事 vt.使 ... 配对；使 ... 一致 vi.交配', '1. I thought she was an ideal mate. 我认为她是我的理想配偶。 2. The eagle mourned for his dead mate. 那只鹰为它死去的配偶伤心。 3. He is my soul mate. 他和我性情相投。 4. Who is your best mate at Liverpool? 谁是你在利物浦最好的伙伴? 5. It\'s high time to mate the doves. 现在正是鸽子配对的好时候。 6. Many animals mate in the spring. 许多动物在春天交配。', '过去式: mated 过去分词: mated 现在分词: mating 第三人称单数: mates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('miss', '[mɪs]', 'n.[M-]小姐 vt.想念 vt.错过；漏掉', '1. Miss Williams can read and write French very well. 威廉斯小姐能够很自如地用法语看书和写东西。 2. I do miss the children. The house seems as silent as the tomb without them. 我真想念孩子们。他们不在家里显得太沉静了。 3. It\'s the chance of a lifetime. You shouldn\'t miss it. 这是一生中难得的机会，你不应错过。 4. He listened attentively so as not to miss a single word . 他不想漏掉一个字，所以很用心的听了。', '过去式: missed 过去分词: missed 现在分词: missing 第三人称单数: misses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accordingly', '[ə\'kɔːrdɪŋli]', 'adv.因此；相应地；于是', '1. He was asked to leave the city and accordingly he went. 有人叫他离开该城市，所以他就走了。 2. I have told you the circumstances, so you must act accordingly. 我已将情况告诉你，所以你必须酌情处理。 3. Accordingly, the crowd was sombre and grave. 因之，人群也显出相应的阴郁和庄重。 4. Just tell us the color and design you have in mind. we\'ll change them accordingly. 把您心里想的颜色和式样告诉我们，我们将作相应的修改。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bite', '[baɪt]', 'v.咬；叮；蜇 n.咬；一口；(被咬的)伤痕', '1. Their dog bit a hole in my trousers. 他们的狗把我的裤子咬了个窟窿。 2. They are badly bitten by mosquitoes. 他们被蚊子叮得很厉害。 3. He was taken to the hospital to be treated for snake bite. 他因遭蛇咬而被送到医院治疗。 4. I\'m stuffed, and I can\'t eat another bite. 我很饱了,一口也吃不下了。', '形容词: bitable 名词: biter 过去式: bit 过去分词: bitten/bit 现在分词: biting 第三人称单数: bites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contempt', '[kən\'tempt]', 'n.轻视；轻蔑', '1. Her gesture was indicative of contempt. 她的动作表示轻视。 2. Such behaviour is beneath contempt. 这种行为令人不齿。 3. They showed nothing but contempt for him. 他们对他轻蔑已极。 4. Her behavior underlined her contempt for him. 她的态度清楚地表示了对他的轻蔑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inhibit', '[ɪn\'hɪbɪt]', 'v.抑制；阻止；使不能', '1. You should inhibit wrong desires and impulses. 你应当抑制不正当的欲望和行动。 2. These compounds inhibit microbial growth. 这些化合物能抑制微生物的生长。 3. Why didn\'t you inhibit him from doing that? 为何你不阻止他做那种事? 4. They passed a law to inhibit people from parking in the street. 他们通过一项法令以阻止人们在街上停车。', '形容词: inhibitable 过去式: inhibited 过去分词: inhibited 现在分词: inhibiting 第三人称单数: inhibits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('motor', '[\'moʊtər]', 'n.马达；发动机；机动车 adj.机动的；汽车的；运动神经的', '1. At six o\'clock the motor started up. 6点钟时马达开动起来。 2. If the battery is dead, the motor won\'t turn over. 电池要是用完了，马达就转不起来了。 3. We switched off the motor and started to drift (along). 我们关闭发动机开始滑行。 4. I stopped the car but left the motor ticking over. 我停住汽车，让发动机空转。 5. Last year was really bad for the motor industry in Europe. 去年，欧洲的机动车市场很不景气。', '过去式: motored 过去分词: motored 现在分词: motoring 第三人称单数: motors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ocean', '[\'oʊʃn]', 'n.海洋；海量', '1. These creatures live in the depth of the Pacific Ocean. 这些生物生活在太平洋的海底。 2. The day\'s drive still left us a hundred miles short of the ocean. 我们整天驱车，但离大海还有100英里。 3. It\'s almost impossible to find him in the immense ocean. 在无边无际的海洋中要找到他几乎是不可能的。 4. We were drifting on the boundless ocean. 我们在漫无边际的海洋上飘泊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('update', '[ˌʌp\'deɪt]', 'v.更新；升级 n.更新', '1. The data should be updated once a week. 这些数据应该每星期更新一次。 2. The feedback from the computer enables us to update the program. 计算机的反馈能使我们更新程序。 3. I would advise you to update the software. 我建议你把这个软件升级。 4. Maps need regular updates. 地图需要经常修订。', '过去式: updated 过去分词: updated 现在分词: updating 第三人称单数: updates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pillow', '[\'pɪloʊ]', 'n.枕头 vt.枕；搁；垫', '1. He bought a foam pillow. 他买了一个海绵枕头。 2. My daughter asked me to buy her a pillow stuffed with feathers. 我女儿请求我给她买一个羽绒枕头。 3. I want to consult with my pillow before I take a decision. 在我做出决定前，我要好好考虑一下。 4. Her arm pillowed the sleeping child. 熟睡的孩子枕着她的手臂。', '形容词: pillowy 过去式: pillowed 过去分词: pillowed 现在分词: pillowing 第三人称单数: pillows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('candle', '[\'kændl]', 'n.蜡烛；烛形物 vt.对光检查', '1. He put the candle on the silver candlestick. 他把蜡烛放在银烛台上。 2. The candle was blown out by the wind. 蜡烛被风吹灭了。 3. A solitary candle lightened the darkness of the room. 一支孤烛使黑暗的房间亮了起来。 4. She is pretty good, but she can\'t hold a candle to her mother. 她相当不错，但还不能与他母亲相比。 5. To make sure that the eggs are fresh, we had better candle them one by one. 为了查明鸡蛋是否新鲜，我们最好将鸡蛋一一对着光检查一遍。', '名词: candler 过去式: candled 过去分词: candled 现在分词: candling 第三人称单数: candles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('retreat', '[rɪ\'triːt]', 'n.撤退；改变；隐居处 v.撤退；改变；退避；缩回象棋的棋子', '1. The troop made good their retreat from the occupied city. 部队从沦陷的城市安全撤出。 2. He immediately sounded a retreat. 他立刻下令撤退。 3. The minister made an undignified retreat from his earlier position. 那部长很不光彩地背离了他原先的立场。 4. The Senator made an embarrassing retreat from his earlier position. 这位参议员很尴尬地改变了他早先的立场。 5. After several reverses the enemy was forced to retreat. 几经失败之后，敌军被迫后撤。', '名词: retreater 过去式: retreated 过去分词: retreated 现在分词: retreating 第三人称单数: retreats');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compose', '[kəm\'poʊz]', 'v.作曲；创作；编排；形成；使镇静', '1. She began to compose songs at an early age. 她还很年轻时就已经开始创作歌曲。 2. He was composing at the piano at the age of seven. 他7岁时就会钢琴作曲。 3. He sat down and composed a letter of resignation. 他坐下来,写了一封辞职信。 4. It is the law-makers\'s duty to compose laws into a coherent system. 将各项法律编排成为一个连贯的体系是立法者的职责。', '过去式: composed 过去分词: composed 现在分词: composing 第三人称单数: composes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('collision', '[kə\'lɪʒn]', 'n.碰撞；冲突', '1. The car was completely wrecked by the force of the collision. 这辆汽车受到很大的撞击力而完全损坏。 2. The liner is reported to have been in collision with an oil tanker. 据报道，这艘客轮与一艘油轮相撞。 3. The Government and the unions are on a collision course. 政府和工会必将发生冲突。 4. This collision had a very unusual cause. 这次冲突有着非同寻常的原因。', '形容词: collisional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('floor', '[flɔːr]', 'n.地面；地板；楼层；底部 vt.铺地板；击倒；(油门)踩到底', '1. Father asked me to flushed off the garage floor. 父亲让我刷洗一下车库的地面。 2. The floor was moist and slippery. 地面潮湿而光滑。 3. We put the books in piles on the floor. 我们把书在地板上堆起来。 4. Our office is on the first floor. 我们的办公室在一楼。 5. We will floor this room with oak. 我们打算用橡木铺地板。', '名词: floorer 过去式: floored 过去分词: floored 现在分词: flooring 第三人称单数: floors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pants', '[pænts]', 'n.裤子，短裤（名词pant的复数形式） v.气喘吁吁；渴望（动词pant的第三人称单数形式）', '1. He asked the tailor to make over his pants. 他请裁缝把他的裤子翻改了一下。 2. This jacket will match those pants nicely. 这件夹克和那条裤子会十分相配。 3. My old pair of pants has worn thin at the knees. 我那条旧裤子的膝盖处已穿薄了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chew', '[tʃuː]', 'vt.咀嚼；嚼碎；深思 vi.咀嚼 n.咀嚼；咀嚼物', '1. Many people like to chew mint gum in the summer. 许多人喜欢在夏天嚼薄荷口香糖。 2. You must chew your food well before you swallow it. 食物吞下去之前先要细细咀嚼。 3. Chew your food well before swallow. 吞下食物以前必须要好好咀嚼。 4. Chew your food properly before swallowing it. 食物嚼碎後再咽下。 5. Saliva helps one chew and digest food. 唾液能帮助咀嚼和消化食物。 6. I\'ll think about it while I have a chew. 我吃饭时会想想看。', '形容词: chewable 名词: chewer 过去式: chewed 过去分词: chewed 现在分词: chewing 第三人称单数: chews');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spray', '[spreɪ]', 'v.喷雾；喷射；扫射 n.喷雾；喷雾器；水沫', '1. He sprayed paint on the wall. 他把漆喷在墙上。 2. We should spray some hairspray on your hair. 我们应该喷些发胶在你的头发上。 3. Please spray some water on the flower. 请给花洒些水。 4. The gangsters sprayed the car with machinegun bullets. 匪徒们用机枪狂扫汽车。 5. I\'ve lost my throat spray. 我的润喉剂喷筒丢了。', '名词: sprayer 过去式: sprayed 过去分词: sprayed 现在分词: spraying 第三人称单数: sprays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heel', '[hiːl]', 'n.脚后跟 v.倾侧', '1. His heel is raw because his shoe does not fit well. 因鞋子不合适，他的脚后跟擦破皮了。 2. I have a blister on my heel because my shoes are too tight. 鞋子太紧了，我脚后跟起了个泡。 3. He was about to crush the plant with his heel, when a new thought made him stop. 他正想要用脚后跟践碎那株小草,而一个新的的念头使他停下来了。 4. The boat heeled the strong wind. 船在大风吹袭下倾到了一边。', '过去式: heeled 过去分词: heeled 现在分词: heeling 第三人称单数: heels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ecology', '[i\'kɑːlədʒi]', 'n.生态学；生态', '1. Ecology helps us understand complex problems. 生态学帮助我们把握复杂问题。 2. He started to study ecology and decided to devote his whole life to the science. 他开始研究生态学,并决心将他的一生献身于这门学科。 3. Fossils allow us to reconstruct ancient ecology. 化石可以让我们知道古时的生态环境。 4. Concern about ecology is a recent development. 对生态的关心是最近才有的事。', '形容词: ecological 副词: ecologically 名词: ecologist 名词复数: ecologies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('negative', '[\'neɡətɪv]', 'adj.否定的；消极的；负面的；负的 n.否定；反面意见；底片；[数]负数 vt.否定', '1. Now I am afraid of getting a negative response. 现在真害怕收到否定的答复。 2. You can\'t learn anything with negative attitude. 你用消极的态度什么也学不到。 3. He conducted a negative campaign against his opponent. 他对他的对手进行了负面打击。 4. This negative pressure phase is of short duration. 负压周期的延续时间很短。 5. The answer to my request was in the negative. 对我的请求的答复是否定的。 6. The government negatived our request for financing. 政府否决了我们融资的请求。', '副词: negatively 名词: negativeness 过去式: negatived 过去分词: negatived 现在分词: negativing 第三人称单数: negatives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('manifest', '[\'mænɪfest]', 'vt.显示；证实；表露 adj.明白的；显然的 n.旅客名单；载货单', '1. His generosity manifests itself in times of difficulties. 他的慷慨在困境中表现了出来。 2. Opportunities will manifest in ways you never even dreamed of. 机会的到来出乎你的意料。 3. No one can manifest the truth of his statement. 没人能证明他讲的是真话。 4. The contradiction manifested itself in the employment situation. 在就业问题上矛盾暴露了。 5. It was manifest to us at a glance. 我们对此事一目了然。 6. Can you give us a copy of import manifest? 能给我们一份进口舱单吗?', '副词: manifestly 过去式: manifested 过去分词: manifesed 现在分词: manifesting 第三人称单数: manifests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('capture', '[\'kæptʃər]', 'vt.捕获；占领；夺取；吸引；(用照片等)留存 n.捕获；战利品', '1. The animals are captured in nets and sold to local zoos. 那些动物用网捕获后被卖到当地的动物园。 2. Rebel forces finally captured the village. 叛军最终占领了这个村庄。 3. The company looks forward to capturing the Canadian market. 该公司期待获得加拿大市场。 4. The novel captured the imagination of thousands of readers. 这部小说引起了千万读者的想象。 5. The revolutionist eluded capture for weeks by hiding underground. 那位革命者为避免被捕在地下躲藏了几个星期。', '过去式: captured 过去分词: captured 现在分词: capturing 第三人称单数: captures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expense', '[ɪk\'spens]', 'n.费用；花费；代价', '1. It\'s too much of an expense for me to own a car. 对我来说，拥有一辆汽车的花费太大。 2. Societies should try to save every plant and animal species, regardless of the expense to humans in effort, time, and financial well-being. 社会应尽力挽救每一动植物物种,不管花费多少人力、时间和财力。 3. Don\'t involve yourself in unnecessary expense. 勿做不必要的花费。 4. He finished the job at the expenses of his health. 他以牺牲健康完成了这项工作。', '过去式: expensed 过去分词: expensed 现在分词: expensing 第三人称单数: expenses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('saturate', '[\'sætʃəreɪt]', 'v.使浸透；使充满；使饱和 adj.浸透的；饱和的；深颜色的', '1. We lay on the beach, saturated in sunshine. 我们躺在沙滩上，沐浴在阳光里。 2. We were caught in the rain and came home saturated. 我们挨了雨淋, 回家时已浑身湿透。 3. The air was saturated with the perfume of the flowers. 空气中飘荡着花香。 4. The films manufactured by Hollywood are saturated in the cinemas all over the world. 在全世界电影市场上充斥着好莱坞的影片。', '形容词: saturable 名词: saturator 过去式: saturated 过去分词: saturated 现在分词: saturating 第三人称单数: saturates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forge', '[fɔːrdʒ]', 'vt.锻造；伪造；建立 vi.伪造；做铁匠 n.锻炉；铁匠铺；锻造车间', '1. These machine parts have been forged with the finest steel. 这些机器零件得用优质的钢锻造。 2. George was forced to forge a signature. 乔治被迫伪造签名。 3. They forged their manager\'s signature on the cheque. 他们在支票上伪造了经理的签名。 4. They tried to forge an alliance. 他们试图建立同盟。 5. Some people forge official documents. 有些人伪造公文。 6. He began to heat, like iron in the forge. 他象锻炉里的铁一样热起来。', '形容词: forgeable 名词: forgeability 过去式: forged 过去分词: forged 现在分词: forging 第三人称单数: forges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('militant', '[\'mɪlɪtənt]', 'adj.好战的；积极从事或支持使用武力的 n.斗士；激进分子', '1. We have militant bonds of friendship. 我们有战斗情谊。 2. We have never been so inspired and militant. 我们从来没有像现在这样意气风发,斗志昂扬。 3. The speaker is shouted down by militant union members. 演讲者被富有战斗精神的工会会员声音所压倒。 4. The militant group has suspected links to al-Qaeda. 该组织被怀疑与基地组织有关联。 5. Our Militant Life is Like a Poem. 我们的战斗生活像诗篇。', '副词: militantly 名词: militance');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('slice', '[slaɪs]', 'n.薄片；部分；曲球 v.切成薄片；割；切开', '1. Please give me a slice of bread. 请给我一片面包。 2. This is just a slice of life. 这只是人生的一个片段罢了。 3. He also gets a slice of the profit. 他也得到一份利润。 4. A slice is a curving shot from left to right with severe sidespin. 右曲球是一种带有相当于顺时钟旋转导致剧烈向右弯曲的击球。 5. Slice the mushrooms thinly and fry in butter. 把蘑菇切成薄片,用黄油抄。', '形容词: sliceable 名词: slicer 过去式: sliced 过去分词: sliced 现在分词: slicing 第三人称单数: slices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('baseball', '[\'beɪsbɔːl]', 'n.棒球', '1. Rain interrupted our baseball game. 下雨中断了我们的捧球比赛。 2. Baseball is the national game of the USA. 棒球是美国全民喜爱的运动。 3. We\'re rooting for the college baseball team. 我们在给学院的棒球队加油。 4. Baseball is more popular than any other sport in Japan. 在日本，棒球比其他任何运动都受人欢迎。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('life', '[laɪf]', 'n.一生；生命；生活；人生', '1. Surely, I will keep the secret for my whole life. 当然,我会一生保守这个秘密。 2. He had a car accident and his life was in danger. 他遭遇车祸,有生命危险。 3. I prefer country life to city life. 我喜爱乡村生活,不喜爱城市生活。 4. As we know, life is often compared with a voyage. 如我们所知道的,人生常被比做航海。', '名词复数: lives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('handwriting', '[\'hændraɪtɪŋ]', 'n.笔迹；书法', '1. The handwriting on both cheques is identical. 两张支票上的笔迹完全相同。 2. It\'s always a problem deciphering his handwriting. 辨认他的笔迹有困难。 3. My handwriting cannot compete with his. 我的书法不及他。 4. There is need for improvement in your handwriting. 你的书法需要改进。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eccentric', '[ɪk\'sentrɪk]', 'adj.古怪的；反常的；不同圆心的 n.怪人；[物]偏心轮', '1. The old lady is a bit of an eccentric. 这位老太是个有点古怪的人。 2. She put him down as an eccentric person. 她认为他是个行为古怪的人。 3. His actions since that morning have been eccentric and unpredictable. 自从那天早晨,他的行动一直是反常而不可捉摸。 4. The motors and drive units on these two types of polisher\'s oscillate in an eccentric circular motion. 发动机和转速单位在这两种抛光机上的振蒎是一个偏圆心的运动。 5. He had the name of an eccentric. 他有怪人之称。', '副词: eccentrically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('effective', '[ɪ\'fektɪv]', 'adj.有效的；生效的；实际的', '1. Advertising is often the most effective method of promotion. 做广告往往是最有效的推销方法。 2. Their efforts to improve the production have been very effective. 他们提高生产力的措施卓有成效。 3. When does the new system become effective? 新制度何时生效？ 4. Her brother is the king, but she is the effective ruler. 她的兄弟是国王, 但她才是实际的主宰者。', '名词: effectiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('implicit', '[ɪm\'plɪsɪt]', 'adj.含蓄的；绝对的；无疑问的；固有的；无保留的；暗示的', '1. Her attitude was implicit in the answer she gave us. 她在给我们的答复中态度是含蓄的。 2. The system of rules implicit in a language, viewed as a mechanism for generating all sentences possible in that language. 语法规则隐含在一种语言中的规则体系，被看作在该语言中生成所有可能的语句的机制 3. The crew had implicit faith in the captain\'s judgment. 全体船员都绝对相信船长的判断。 4. The oak is implicit in the acorn. 橡实是橡树固有的。', '副词: implicitly 名词: implicitness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stride', '[straɪd]', 'n.大步走；一大步；步伐；进步 vt.跨；跨骑 vi.迈大步走；跨过；分腿站立', '1. In a few strides he crossed the room. 他几大步就穿过了房间。 2. I was three strides from the door. 我距离那门有三大步远。 3. In a big stride he came out of the room. 他一个箭步出了房间。 4. The boy walked with a confident manly stride. 这男孩以自信的男人步伐行走。 5. The boy is too young to stride the ditch. 孩子太小跨不过这条沟。 6. China is striding ahead in her economic construction. 中国正在经济建设方面大步前进。', '名词: strider 过去式: strode 过去分词: stridden 现在分词: striding 第三人称单数: strides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tank', '[tæŋk]', 'n.箱；罐；槽；贮水池；坦克 vt.把 ... 储于槽中', '1. Is there any water left in the water tank? 水箱里还有水剩下吗？ 2. The gas is stored under pressure in the tank. 该气体在压缩状态下贮存于罐中。 3. I need a funnel to pour petrol into the tank. 我需要一个漏斗把汽油灌进油箱。 4. Gasoline dribbled from the leak in the tank. 汽油从油槽漏隙滴下。 5. Will you tank up my car immediately? 请你立即给我的汽车加满油好吗?', '形容词: tankless 名词: tankful 过去式: tanked 过去分词: tanked 现在分词: tanking 第三人称单数: tanks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('woman', '[\'wʊmən]', 'n.妇女；女人 adj.女人的', '1. She is a career woman rather than a housewife. 她是职业妇女而不是家庭主妇。 2. The chief conductor turned out to be a young woman. 列车长原来是一位青年妇女。 3. She seems a pleasant woman. 她似乎是一个友善的女人。 4. Her mother is a woman with great refinement. 她母亲是一个非常文雅的女人。', '形容词: womanless 名词复数: women');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('frown', '[fraʊn]', 'n.皱眉；不悦 v.不同意；皱眉头', '1. We interpret a frown as a sign of disapproval. 我们把皱眉当作不赞成的表示。 2. The frown on the man\'s face showed that he was displeased. 那人皱着眉头，面露不悦。 3. There was a deep frown of his face. 他的额头深深的皱眉。 4. Her beautiful face had a resentful frown on it. 她那俊俏的眉梢怨恨地蹙了起来。 5. He would frown on such a proposal. 他不会赞成这样的建议。', '副词: frowningly 名词: frowner 过去式: frowned 过去分词: frowned 现在分词: frowning 第三人称单数: frowns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('activity', '[æk\'tɪvəti]', 'n.活动；活跃 vt.表演 adj.厉害', '1. We love outdoor activity. 我们热爱户外活动。 2. We plan to expand our business activities in East Africa. 我们打算在东非扩展我们的商业活动。 3. The volcano is in activity. 这火山正活跃著。 4. There was a sudden spurt of activity in the housing market. 房产市场突然活跃了一阵子。 5. Busking is a fun activity for the performer. 街头表演对于街头艺人来说是一项有乐趣的活动。', '名词复数: activities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('keyboard', '[\'kiːbɔːrd]', 'n.键盘 v.用键盘输入', '1. The computer has a normal qwerty keyboard. 这台计算机有标准的英文键盘。 2. You will be asked to choose your keyboard layout. 将让你选择键盘布局。 3. You can type in the command with a keyboard. 你可以用键盘输入命令。 4. In earlier days, the video display was used solely to echo text that the user typed using the keyboard. 早些时候，视频显示器仅仅用来回显用户用键盘输入的文本。', '名词: keyboarder 过去式: keyboarded 过去分词: keyboarded 现在分词: keyboarding 第三人称单数: keyboards');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('repertoire', '[\'repərtwɑːr]', 'n.全部节目；全部才能', '1. A repertoire of tricks will astound the esteemed public. 全部节目将使尊敬的观众惊心动魄。 2. That tune is not in my repertoire. 我演出的节目中没有这个曲子。 3. He has a wide repertoire of dirty jokes. 他一肚子下流笑话. 4. Julia has a vast repertoire of smiles. 朱莉娅具有驾御各式微笑的本领。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pan', '[pæn]', 'n.平底锅；盘子；盘状物；淘盘；<俚>脸；严厉批评 v.严厉批评；（用淘盘）淘金', '1. I cracked two eggs into the frying pan. 我往平底锅里打了两个鸡蛋。 2. Take a pan or box and fill it with sand or cat litter. 拿一个盘子或盒子，里面装上沙子或者干草。 3. The water was run off from the pan so that the sand remained. 把淘盘里的水放掉，让沙留着。 4. They dip the pan into the bed of the stream, and then pan out the sand and dirt, hoping that some gold will be left. 他们用淘盘舀出小溪溪底泥沙，然后淘去泥沙，希望有金子留下来。 5. His new film was really panned by the critics. 他新拍摄的电影确实受到评论家严厉的批评。', '过去式: panned 过去分词: panned 现在分词: panning 第三人称单数: pans');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('perplex', '[pər\'pleks]', 'v.使困惑；使糊涂；使复杂化', '1. When new math was introduced into schools, many parents were perplexed by it. 当学校开设新的数学课时，许多家长对此感到迷惑不解。 2. Faced with that dilemma, he was perplexed. 他面对进退两难的局面，不知如何是好。', '副词: perplexingly 过去式: perplexed 过去分词: perplexed 现在分词: perplexing 第三人称单数: perplexes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('white', '[waɪt]', 'adj.白色的；纯洁的；白种的；加牛奶的 n.白色；白种人', '1. This parapet is white. 这个栏杆是白色的。 2. He was white with fury. 他气得脸色发白。 3. Borax is a kind of white powder. 硼砂是一种白色粉末。 4. Her reputation is as white as snow. 她的声誉纯洁无瑕。 5. The black shows up against the white. 在白色的衬托下,黑色很显目。', '比较级: whiter 最高级: whitest 名词: whiteness 过去式: whited 过去分词: whited 现在分词: whiting 第三人称单数: whites');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('specimen', '[\'spesɪmən]', 'n.标本；样本', '1. This specimen is richly variegated in colour. 这件标本上有很多颜色。 2. Arthur brought out his specimen box. 亚瑟拿出了他的标本箱。 3. He is still a fine specimen of health. 他仍是健康的典范。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('date', '[deɪt]', 'n.日期；年代；会晤时间；约会；约会对象；枣椰树；枣子 v.给 ... 标明日期；确定年代；过时；显老；和 ... 约会；追溯到', '1. If I pay a fee can I change the date? 如果付费,能够改机票日期吗? 2. What\'s your card number and expiration date? 你的visa卡号码与有效日期呢? 3. This vase is of an earlier date than that one. 这个花瓶的年代比那个的早. 4. They made a date to meet soon. 他们约定不久见面。 5. Don\'t forget to date your cheque. 不要忘记在支票上写上日期。', '形容词: datable 名词: dater 过去式: dated 过去分词: dated 现在分词: dating 第三人称单数: dates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('page', '[peɪdʒ]', 'n.页；页码；侍从 vt.给 ... 标页码 vi.翻页', '1. There are several faults in the page of figures. 那一页的数字中有几个差错。 2. Open your German readers at page 28. 把德语课本翻到第28页。 3. The page number is shown at the foot of the page. 在页脚处可以看到页码。 4. When the book is ready for printing,someone has to page it up. 书在付印前，必须有人排好页码。 5. He tore the sheet in his hurry to turn over the page. 他匆忙翻页的时候，把杂志都撕坏了。', '名词: pageful 过去式: paged 过去分词: paged 现在分词: paging 第三人称单数: pages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suicide', '[\'suːɪsaɪd]', 'n.自杀；自杀者；自取灭亡的行为 adj.自杀性的', '1. For one reason or another, she committed suicide. 不知什么原因，她自杀了。 2. The police suspect foul play rather than suicide. 警方怀疑是谋杀不是自杀。 3. He attempted suicide after his firm had gone bankrupt. 他在公司破产后曾试图自杀。 4. He pulled a would-be suicide out of a river. 他将一位自杀未遂者从河里拖上来。 5. She pretended not to have known the suicide bomber. 她假装不认识那名自杀式炸弹袭击者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grope', '[ɡroʊp]', 'v.(暗中)摸索；探索；<口>(调情时)抚摸…身体', '1. I groped for the door handle in the dark. 我在黑暗中摸索着门把手。 2. We groped our way through the dark streets. 我们摸索着走过黑暗的街道。 3. We have to grope for ways to do thing. 我们只能边探索边干。 4. Just friends. I won\'t grope you, I promise. 只是朋友嘛。我不会对你动手动脚的，我保证。', '副词: gropingly 名词: groper 过去式: groped 过去分词: groped 现在分词: groping 第三人称单数: gropes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('supper', '[\'sʌpər]', 'n.晚饭；晚餐；晚餐会', '1. He had some rice for supper. 晚饭时他吃了一些米饭。 2. I came here immediately after having my supper. 我一吃完晚饭就来这里了。 3. Have you had your supper? 你吃过晚饭了吗？ 4. I\'ll just throw together a quick supper. 我马上做一顿简便的晚餐吧。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('distress', '[dɪ\'stres]', 'n.不幸；危难；苦恼；痛苦 vt.使苦恼；使痛苦', '1. I pray that you will have pity on my distress. 我请求你可怜可怜我的不幸遭遇。 2. I gripe more from habit than from genuine distress. 我抱怨是出于我的习惯，并非遭遇真正的不幸。 3. They sent a distress rocket. 他们发出了一枚呼救信号火箭。 4. His wild behavior was a great distress to his mother. 他的放荡的行为使他的母亲极为苦恼。 5. Don\'t distress yourself about it. 别为那件事苦恼了。', '副词: distressingly 过去式: distressed 过去分词: distressed 现在分词: distressing 第三人称单数: distresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('currency', '[\'kɜːrənsi]', 'n.货币；流通', '1. The president proclaimed that a new currency would be issued. 总统宣布将发行新货币。 2. Our currency will not be depreciated. 我们的货币不会贬值。 3. There are currency restrictions on the sums allowed for foreign travel. 到国外旅行允许携带的款额有所限制。 4. The word has attained general currency. 这个词已经通用起来了。', '名词复数: currencies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('efficient', '[ɪ\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.效率高的；胜任的', '1. This is a highly efficient new heating system. 这是个高效的新取暖系统。 2. Consequently, we have been developing a more efficient engine. 结果,我们已经开发了一台更高性能的发动机。 3. The success of CAD systems is becoming more dependent on the efficient drafting. cad系统的成功在很大程度上取决于草图的制图效率。 4. He\'s efficient at his job. 他胜任工作。', '副词: efficiently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exaggerate', '[ɪɡ\'zædʒəreɪt]', 'vt.夸张；夸大；对...言过其实 vi.夸张；夸大其词', '1. Don\'t exaggerate the parallelism between the two cases. 不要夸大那两件事的相似性。 2. The seriousness of the situation has been much exaggerated by the press. 形势的严重性被报纸夸大了。 3. He tends to exaggerate the difficulties. 他往往夸大困难。 4. We should neither exaggerate nor ignore the differences. 虽然我们不能夸大这些不同，但是我们也不能忽视它们的存在。 5. If you exaggerate, you will sound fantastically American. 如果你发音夸张听起来会特别有美国味。', '形容词: exaggerative 副词: exaggeratedly 名词: exaggeration 过去式: exaggerated 过去分词: exaggerated 现在分词: exaggerating 第三人称单数: exaggerates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('popular', '[\'pɑːpjələr]', 'adj.受欢迎的；通俗的；流行的；大众的', '1. Her charm of manner made her very popular. 她风度优雅，备受欢迎。 2. Baseball is more popular than any other sport in Japan. 在日本，棒球比其他任何运动都受人欢迎。 3. He is very interested in what are called popular songs. 他对所谓的流行歌曲很感兴趣。 4. Fashion is a very popular magazine in America. 《时尚》是美国很流行的杂志。', '副词: popularly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('many', '[\'meni]', 'adj.许多的 pron.许多人或物 n.许多；许多人', '1. Many of these substances are innocuous. 这里的许多物质都无害。 2. A good many of beggars are blind. 乞丐中有许多人是盲人。 3. There are men here from all over the country. Many of them are from the south. 从全国各地来的人中有许多是南方人。', '比较级: more 最高级: most');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nail', '[neɪl]', 'n.钉子；指甲；爪 vt.钉；抓住；使固定', '1. He hit the nail into the wall with a hammer. 他用一把锤子把钉子打进墙里去。 2. I found a nail sticking in the tyre. 我发现轮胎上扎着一根钉子。 3. You can try this nail polish on your nails. 您可以在指甲上试试这种指甲油。 4. She was paring her nails with nail scissors. 她正在用指甲刀修指甲。 5. I will nail up the new pictures on the wall. 我会把这些新的图画钉在墙上。', '名词: nailer 过去式: nailed 过去分词: nailed 现在分词: nailing 第三人称单数: nails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intuition', '[ˌɪntu\'ɪʃn]', 'n.直觉；直觉的知识', '1. He takes his ground on intuition. 他的意见是凭直觉。 2. She sensed what was wrong by intuition. 她凭直觉意识到什么地方出毛病了。 3. It was said in a flash of intuition. 这话是凭一刹那的直觉说出的。 4. She had an intuition that her friend was ill. 她有一种直觉:她的朋友病了。', '形容词: intuitional 副词: intuitionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('segregate', '[\'seɡrɪɡeɪt]', 'v.分离；隔离；分凝 adj.分离的', '1. Why should the handicappedbe segregated from the able-bodied? 为什么要把伤残人士和身体健康的人分开? 2. Some societies still segregate men and women. 有的社会仍然将男女隔离。 3. Mixture of black powder and magnesium has a tendency to segregate. 黑药和镁的混合物具有离析的倾向。', '形容词: segregative 名词: segregator 过去式: segregated 过去分词: segregated 现在分词: segregating 第三人称单数: segregates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strain', '[streɪn]', 'n.拉紧；紧张；血统；笔调；（动植物或疾病的）品种 v.拉紧；劳累；过分使用', '1. The rope finally broke under the strain. 绷紧的绳子终于断了。 2. The tugs took up the strain and the ocean liner edged away from the quayside. 拖船开始拉紧了，远洋客轮徐徐离开了码头。 3. All her senses were on the strain when the test was going on. 测试时，她所有的感官都处于紧张状态。 4. A sudden and severe strain was placed upon us by the cutting off of these supplies. 由于供给突然被切断，我们感到了沉重的压力。 5. Too heavy a load will strain the rope to its breaking point. 负载过重会把绳子拉紧到崩断的地步。', '过去式: strained 过去分词: strained 现在分词: straining 第三人称单数: strains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('meditate', '[\'medɪteɪt]', 'v.沉思；冥想；考虑；计划', '1. He meditates on his past life. 他沉思着过去的生活。 2. These fields had subtle aromas that I loved to sit and meditate in. 这些田野散发淡淡的芳香，我喜欢坐在那里冥想。 3. I hope you can meditate it before you make decision . 我希望你做决定前仔细考虑一下。 4. Clever people should meditate on the problems before acting. 聪明的人应该是在采取行动前先仔细考虑一下。', '名词: meditator 过去式: meditated 过去分词: meditated 现在分词: meditating 第三人称单数: meditates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('frame', '[freɪm]', 'n.骨架；身躯；结构；框；帧 v.表达；制定；把 ... 框起来；陷害', '1. She is having a lean, gaunt frame with prominent bones. 他骨瘦如柴的身材又细又瘦,骨骼突出的 2. Sobs shook her slender frame. 她抽泣著，苗条的身体都在颤动。 3. This athlete has a powerful frame. 这位运动员有着魁梧的体格。 4. It gives the frame of DFL programming language. 提出了DFL程序设计语言的基本框架结构。 5. His lips could hardly frame the words. 他几乎说不出话来。', '过去式: framed 过去分词: framed 现在分词: framing 第三人称单数: frames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('react', '[ri\'ækt]', 'v.反应；反攻', '1. Iron reacts with water and air to produce rust. 铁与水和空气起化学反应而生锈。 2. She reacted to the insult by turning her back on him. 她受辱之后就不再理睬他了。 3. How did they react to your suggestion? 他们对你的建议有什么反应？ 4. An acid can react with a base to form a salt. 酸可以和碱起反应而生成盐。', '过去式: reacted 过去分词: reacted 现在分词: reacting 第三人称单数: reacts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('juice', '[dʒuːs]', 'n.果汁；肉汁；消化液；汽油；精力 vt.挤出汁来；使有活力', '1. I like to drink coconut juice. 我喜欢喝椰子汁。 2. She was drinking juice through a straw. 她正在用吸管喝果汁。 3. Give the bottle a couple of shakes before pouring the juice. 倒果汁前，先把瓶子摇几下。 4. Would you like some tomato juice? 你想要些番茄汁吗？ 5. She juiced an orange for her breakfast. 她用一只橙子榨汁作早餐饮料。', '过去式: juiced 过去分词: juiced 现在分词: juicing 第三人称单数: juices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('turn', '[tɜːrn]', 'v.翻转；旋转；转动；转向；轮流；（使）变得 n.轮流；转动', '1. The turbulence caused the plane to turn over. 空气的激流导致飞机翻转。 2. Men carried corpses in blankets away from the scene and a dozen others tried to turn over a car with two bodies beneath. 搬运工把用毯子盖着的尸体搬离现场，另有十多人试图翻转汽车，搬出下面的两具尸体。 3. At each turn the screw goes in further. 每一次旋转都使螺丝钉更向里进。 4. She got up and spun a little turn. 她站起身来，打了个小旋转。 5. It is now his turn to set me up to a nice dinner. 现在轮到他请我吃一顿丰盛的晚餐了。', '过去式: turned 过去分词: turned 现在分词: turning 第三人称单数: turns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nowadays', '[\'naʊədeɪz]', 'adv.现今；现在', '1. Nowadays we rely increasingly on computers for help/to help us. 现今人们越来越依赖计算机协助工作。 2. Nowadays people travel in cars rather than carriages. 现今人们旅行都坐汽车，而不使用马车。 3. Portable telephones are very popular nowadays. 现今，移动电话非常普及。 4. Nowadays, children often prefer watching TV to reading. 如今，儿童常爱看电视而不爱看书。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('problem', '[\'prɑːbləm]', 'n.问题；难题；习题 adj.成问题的；难对付的', '1. That\'s your problem. 那是你的问题。 2. We had no time to deliberate on the problem. 我们没有时间仔细思考这个问题. 3. The problem is when to get the money we need. 问题是什么时候能得到我们所需要的钱。 4. Heavy traffic poses a problem in many old towns. 交通拥挤是许多旧城镇的难题。 5. Today\'s problem child may be tomorrow\'s criminal. 今天的问题孩子可能就是明天的罪犯。', '名词复数: problems');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rise', '[raɪz]', 'vi.上升；升起；增加；起床；反抗；复活 n.上升；增加；斜坡；小山', '1. The sun heats the earth, causing the air to rise and the winds to blow. 太阳给地球热量,引起空气上升,刮起风来。 2. The higher we rise, the smaller we appear to those who do not know how to fly. 我们上升得越高,我们在那些不懂飞翔的人眼里就显得越遥远。 3. The sun rises in the east and sets in the west. 太阳从东方升起，在西方落下。 4. In proportion as the sales increase the profit will rise. 随着销售量增长,利润也成比例地增加。 5. I am reading a book about the rise and fall of the Roman Empire. 我正在看一本关于罗马帝国兴衰的书。', '过去式: rose 过去分词: risen 现在分词: rising 第三人称单数: rises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('march', '[mɑːrtʃ]', 'n.行军；行进；游行示威；稳步前进；进行曲 v.行进；前进；进发；使同行；游行示威 March n.三月', '1. Not a single man fell out in the long march. 在长途行军中没有一个人掉队。 2. The army was now on the march to Shanghai. 部队当时正向上海进军。 3. Science is on the march. 科学正在进步中。 4. The peace march attracted a large turnout. 和平游行吸引了大量的参加者。 5. The shower being over, we continued to march. 阵雨过去之后我们继续行进。 6. This term will begin on March 1st. 这个学期三月一日开始。', '过去式: marched 过去分词: marched 现在分词: marching 第三人称单数: marches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('screen', '[skriːn]', 'n.屏幕；银幕；隔板；屏风；掩蔽物；纱窗；纱门；筛子 v.掩蔽；包庇；放映；筛；检查', '1. The advertisement is full of the TV screen today. 今天，电视屏幕被广告占据。 2. Buzz suddenly appeared on my computer screen. 巴兹突然出现在我的电脑屏幕上。 3. Familiar scenes were imaged on the screen. 银幕上映出了熟悉的景象。 4. Someday I will be a star on the big screen. 有一天我将成为大银幕上的明星。 5. The curtains screen out the sunlight. 窗帘遮住了阳光。', '形容词: screenable 名词: screener 过去式: screened 过去分词: screened 现在分词: screening 第三人称单数: screens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('judicial', '[dʒu\'dɪʃl]', 'adj.司法的；法庭的；公正的；审判上的', '1. He applied for judicial review to quash the order. 他申请司法检查废止该命令。 2. She got a judicial separation from her husband. 她得到法庭判决夫妇分居。 3. He is a man with a judicial mind. 他是个公正的人。 4. In British India, district commissioners had judicial powers. 在过去的英属印度，地区长官有审判权。', '副词: judicially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('decorate', '[\'dekəreɪt]', 'v.装饰；布置；装修；授予某人奖章或其他奖状', '1. We decorated the house for Christmas. 我们装饰房屋过圣诞节。 2. My mother likes to decorate rooms. 我妈妈非常喜欢装饰房间。 3. I\'ll bring some balloons to decorate. 我要带些气球去装饰装饰。 4. May I help you decorate the room? 我可以帮你装饰布置房间吗？', '过去式: decorated 过去分词: decorated 现在分词: decorating 第三人称单数: decorates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('resent', '[rɪ\'zent]', 'vt.恨；生气', '1. Kate said she felt we resent her. 凯特说她感到我们大家恨她。 2. I resent the encroachment on my time. 我讨厌别人侵占我的时间。 3. I bitterly resent his attempts to interfere in my work. 我非常讨厌他企图干涉我的工作。 4. I resent having to get his permission for everything I do. 我讨厌做每件事都要得到他的许可。', '过去式: resented 过去分词: resented 现在分词: resenting 第三人称单数: resents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('guitar', '[ɡɪ\'tɑːr]', 'n.吉他', '1. He plays the guitar and sings too. 他会弹吉他，也会唱歌。 2. I write my own songs and I play the guitar as well. 我唱自己谱曲的歌，也弹吉他。 3. It is fun to play the guitar. 弹吉他是好玩的。 4. He sat there strumming a guitar. 他坐在那儿漫不经心地弹吉他。', '名词: guitarist');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('luck', '[lʌk]', 'n.运气；幸运；侥幸 v.侥幸成功；走运', '1. He came to Beijing to try his luck. 他来到北京，想碰碰运气。 2. He had wonderful luck in all his ventures. 他干任何事情运气都好。 3. He ascribes his success to good luck. 他把他的成功归功于幸运。 4. You never know your luck. 你也许会走运的。 5. Don\'t expect to luck through without an effort. 别指望不经努力就能侥幸成功。', '过去式: lucked 过去分词: lucked 现在分词: lucking 第三人称单数: lucks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('improvement', '[ɪm\'pruːvmənt]', 'n.改进；改善', '1. I see little prospect of an improvement in his condition. 我看他的情况没有什么改进的希望。 2. There is need for improvement in your handwriting. 你的书法需要改进。 3. Housing improvement was the speaker\'s text. 改善住房是那位演讲人的题目。 4. The situation is capable of improvement. 这种情况是可以改善的.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jump', '[dʒʌmp]', 'n.跳跃；跳动；上涨 v.跳越；暴涨', '1. If a horse refuses a jump,penalty points are added to the score. 如果马拒绝跳跃，是要扣分的。 2. The athlete made a superb jump. 运动运做了一个出色的跳跃。 3. The loud bang made me jump. 砰的一声巨响吓了我一跳。 4. The jump in food prices gave rise to a lot of complaint. 食品价格的猛涨引起了许多不满。 5. The horse was behaving fractiously and refused to jump. 这匹马很倔强，拒绝跳越。', '过去式: jumped 过去分词: jumped 现在分词: jumping 第三人称单数: jumps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('motivate', '[\'moʊtɪveɪt]', 'vt.激发(兴趣或欲望)；给与动机', '1. He is just sitting there doing nothing. He needs to be motivated. 他坐在那儿什么也不干,他需要一点动力去激发他。 2. The crime appears to have been motivated by hatred. 犯罪似乎都来自于仇恨。 3. A good teacher is one who can motivate his students. 好老师是能激励学生的老师。', '名词: motivator 过去式: motivated 过去分词: motivated 现在分词: motivating 第三人称单数: motivates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('historian', '[hɪ\'stɔːriən]', 'n.历史学家；编史者', '1. A good historian must have an academic mind. 出色的历史学家须有学术头脑。 2. Tacitus was the greatest historian in Ancient Rome. 塔西陀是古罗马最伟大的历史学家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intelligent', '[ɪn\'telɪdʒənt]', 'adj.聪明的；智能的', '1. Though very intelligent, she is nevertheless rather modest. 她很聪明，倒也很谦虚。 2. The student gave an intelligent answer. 这个学生给出了一个聪明的回答。 3. Maybe the earth has been visited by intelligent creatures from outer space. 也许太空的智慧生物已经访问过地球。', '形容词: intelligential 副词: intelligently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('associate', '[ə\'soʊʃieɪt]', 'vt.联想；联合 n.伙伴；同事；同伴 adj.副的；共事的；有联系的 n.准学士学位获得者 vi.交往', '1. I always associate her with roses. 我总是把她与玫瑰花联想在一起。 2. We should associate ourselves with this large firm. 我们应该和这家大公司联合。 3. Mr. Miller is a business associate of our company. 米勒先生是我们公司的生意伙伴。 4. I got a new job and a new group of work associates. 我有了新工作和一班新同事。 5. He is an associate editor of the newspaper. 他是报纸的副主编。 6. You are wooing troubles if you associate with him. 你和他交往会招来麻烦。', '过去式: associated 过去分词: associated 现在分词: associating 第三人称单数: associates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trial', '[\'traɪəl]', 'n.审讯；试验；试用；尝试；预赛或选拔赛；讨厌的事；惹麻烦的人 v.测试', '1. He went through hell during the trial. 审讯期间他吃尽了苦头。 2. The flier is flying a new-type jet plane on trial. 飞行员正在驾驶一架新式喷气机作试验飞行。 3. She agreed to employ me for a trial period. 她同意试用我一段时间。 4. Trial and error is the source of our knowledge. 尝试和失败同是学识之源。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attain', '[ə\'teɪn]', 'v.实现；获得；达到', '1. We can attain whatever goal we set in our mind. 我们设定了什么目标，就能实现什么目标。 2. We should be able to attain that goal. 我们应该能够实现这个目标。 3. The country attained its independence in 1972. 这个国家在1972年获得了独立。 4. They\'re sure to attain emancipation in the end. 他们最后一定能获得解放。', '形容词: attainable 名词: attainability 过去式: attained 过去分词: attained 现在分词: attaining 第三人称单数: attains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evolution', '[ˌiːvə\'luːʃn]', 'n.进化；发展；演变', '1. Charles Darwin and Alfred Russell Wallace discovered evolution independently. 查尔斯·达尔文和阿尔弗雷德· 罗素·华莱士各自独立地发现了进化论。 2. Within 30 years,humans could be debating whether to take charge of their own evolution. 不出30年，人类将讨论是否要掌控自身的进化。 3. Our watchword is: ‘Evolution, not revolution’. 我们的口号是: ‘要循序渐进,不要剧烈变革’。 4. Our political institutions are in continuous evolution. 我们的政治制度正在不断发展中。', '形容词: evolutional 副词: evolutionarily');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coalition', '[ˌkoʊə\'lɪʃn]', 'n.结合；联合；联盟', '1. There is no coalition of members of the economy. 这种经济的各部门之间不存在联合。 2. The two parties have united to form a coalition. 这两个党已结成联盟。 3. After the election, the coalition fragmented. 选举之后，联盟瓦解了', '名词: coalitionist');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('apparent', '[ə\'pærənt]', 'adj.明显的；表面上的', '1. It was apparent to all that he was guilty. 众所周知，他是有罪的。 2. Japan\'s apparent lack of capitalist endeavour also has much to do with the lack of a mature financing market. 显而易见,日本缺少资本家的创业精神,而这与日本没有一个成熟的融资市场也有很大关系。 3. She had many good qualities despite her apparent rudeness. 她粗鲁是粗鲁，但还有许多优秀品质。 4. If she had inner doubts, it was not apparent to anyone else. 她若心中生疑亦不形之于色。', '副词: apparently 名词: apparentness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('each', '[iːtʃ]', 'pron.每个；个人；个自 adj.每；每个 adv.每个', '1. We each have our private views about it. 我们每个人对这件事都有自己的看法。 2. I asked all the children and each told a different story. 我问过所有的孩子，每个人的说法都不一样。 3. Each of them had his little local personal history. 他们每一个人都有过一段默默无闻的个人历史。 4. We each paid our share of the bill for the meal. 我们各自付了自己应付的那份饭钱。 5. Each day passed without any news. 每天都没有任何消息.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stamp', '[stæmp]', 'n.邮票；图章；印；跺脚 v.跺脚；盖章', '1. My husband is a stamp collector. 我丈夫是个集邮者。 2. He is looking for his rubber stamp. 他正在找他的橡皮印章。 3. Please bring a photograph of yourself.We have to affix a stamp on the corner of it. 请带一张你的照片来,我们要在它的角上盖个印儿。 4. His face bears the stamp of suffering. 他的脸上有饱经苦难的烙印。 5. She stamped on the insect and killed it. 她踩死了一只虫子。', '过去式: stamped 过去分词: stamped 现在分词: stamping 第三人称单数: stamps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aid', '[eɪd]', 'n.援助；帮助；救援；助手；辅助物 v.辅助；援助；接济', '1. The regime has been propped up by foreign aid. 该政权是靠外国援助维持着的。 2. Filled with fears all day long, he decided to seek the aid of a psychiatrist. 他终日恐惧不安,决定寻求心理医生的帮助。 3. In his father\'s presidential race in 1988, George W. Bush became his father\'s aid. 1988年在他父亲竞选总统时,小布什成为父亲的助手。 4. A dictionary is an invaluable aid in learning a new language. 在学习一种新语言时,辞典是非常有用的工具。 5. We were greatly aided in our investigation by the cooperation of the police. 我们在调查的过程中得到警方的大力协助。', '名词: aider 过去式: aided 过去分词: aided 现在分词: aiding 第三人称单数: aids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('revenge', '[rɪ\'vendʒ]', 'n.报仇；报复；报复心；雪耻机会 vt.报复；报仇', '1. They vowed revenge on their enemies. 他们发誓要向敌人报仇。 2. She said she would take her revenge on Tom. 她说她要向汤姆报仇。 3. Thoughts of revenge kept running through his mind. 他脑海里时刻萦绕着复仇的念头。 4. I want revenge against her on more scores than one. 我有种种理由要向她报复。 5. They thirsted to revenge themselves upon the enemy. 他们渴望向敌人报复。', '名词: revenger 过去式: revenged 过去分词: revenged 现在分词: revenging 第三人称单数: revenges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('masculine', '[\'mæskjəlɪn]', 'adj.男性的；有男子气概的；阳性的 n.阳性；男性', '1. This coat is masculine. 这件外衣是男式的。 2. She looks rather masculine in that suit. 她穿着那套衣服看上去有些男性化。 3. He was handsome and strong, and very masculine. 他英俊强壮，富有男子汉气概。 4. This noun subscribes to the masculine gender. 这个名词是阳性名词。 5. Host is the masculine noun for hostess. host是与hostess相对应的阳性名词。', '副词: masculinely 名词: masculineness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fist', '[fɪst]', 'n.拳头 vt.紧握；用拳头打', '1. He shook his fist at me. 他对我挥舞着拳头。 2. I clenched my fist and hit him. 我攥紧拳头向他击去。 3. He was banging on the door with his fist. 他用拳头砸门。 4. He banged his fist on the table to emphasize his argument. 他用拳头敲着桌子为自己的辩驳助威。 5. You cannot shake hands with a clenched fist. 紧握的拳头不能够和别人握手。', '过去式: fisted 过去分词: fisted 现在分词: fisting 第三人称单数: fists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dependent', '[dɪ\'pendənt]', 'adj.依靠的；依赖的；从属的', '1. All is dependent on your decision. 一切看你的决心而定。 2. The child is dependent on his parents for support. 这个小孩靠他的父母养活。 3. She is still financially dependent on her parents. 她在经济上仍然依靠父母。 4. The country\'s economy is dependent on tourism. 该国经济依赖於旅游业。', '副词: dependently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strong', '[strɔːŋ]', 'adj.强烈的；坚强的；强壮的；强劲的；强大的；确凿的；有影响力的；坚定的；浓的；浓烈的；结实的；可能性大的；擅长的；大量的；稳固的；坚挺的；景气的；强硬的；重读的', '1. A strong light impinged on his eyes. 一道强烈的光刺着他的眼睛。 2. She has a strong desire to become a writer. 她有成为作家的强烈愿望。 3. Such tendentious statements are likely to provoke strong opposition. 这种有倾向性的说法可能招致强烈的反对。 4. He has a very strong will. 他意志很坚强。', '形容词: strongish 副词: strongly 比较级: stronger 最高级: strongest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recent', '[\'riːsnt]', 'adj.近来的；新近的', '1. Recent discoveries will bear his prediction out. 近来的种种发现将会证实他的预言。 2. The government\'s control over the newspapers has loosened in recent years. 近年来政府对报纸的控制已经变松了。 3. The teapot looked old but was a recent fake. \"这把茶壶貌似古董,却是一件新近制作的赝品。\" 4. The minister has put a different gloss on recent developments. 部长就局势的最新发展作了另一番解释。', '副词: recently 名词: recency');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('success', '[sək\'ses]', 'n.成功；成就；胜利；成功的人或事', '1. She is responsible for the character part of the hero\'s devoted mother. 她负责这个主人公的忠诚的母亲的角色部分。 2. The school has only been open for six months, so it\'s hard to evaluate its success. 该学校仅开办了六个月, 现在还很难估计它的成就。 3. I am very heartened by her success in the election. 她在竞选中获胜令我大受鼓舞。 4. He wasn\'t a success as a teacher. 他不是个好教师。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unload', '[ˌʌn\'loʊd]', 'vt.卸下；卸货；摆脱 ... 之负担；(大量)倾销；退出（弹药；胶片等） vi.卸下货物；摆脱负担', '1. You can have a rest after you unload the car . 你们卸下车上的货物后可以休息一下。 2. We began to unload the bricks from the car. 我们开始从车上卸下砖块来。 3. Dockers started unloading the ship. 码头工人开始卸货。 4. Mary began to unload her trouble onto her mother. 玛丽开始把她的烦恼告诉她的母亲。 5. The ship is unloading. 船正在卸货。', '名词: unloader 过去式: unloaded 过去分词: unloaded 现在分词: unloading 第三人称单数: unloads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fame', '[feɪm]', 'n.名声；名望 vt.使出名', '1. She won her overnight fame by her first novel. 她的第一部小说使她一举成名。 2. His fidelity brought him good fame. 他的尽职给他带来了好名声。 3. He spent his life searching after fame. 他这个辈子追求名望。 4. Many great men rose from obscurity to fame. 许多伟人都是从卑微变得有名望的。 5. The city is famed for its scenic spots. 该市以风景优美著称。', '过去式: famed 过去分词: famed 现在分词: faming 第三人称单数: fames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('exceedingly', '[ɪk\'siːdɪŋli]', 'adv.非常；极其；极度地；很', '1. He is an exceedingly tedious fellow. 他是一个非常令人生厌的家伙。 2. We found out that he was exceedingly fond of fishing. 我们发现他极其喜欢钓鱼。 3. Herbert drives exceedingly fast. 赫伯特开车过快。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bend', '[bend]', 'v.弯曲；使弯曲；屈服；屈从；集中于 n.弯曲；弯道', '1. The branches bent in the wind. 树枝被风吹弯了。 2. The branch bent but didn\'t break when the boy climbed along it. 那男孩爬上树枝时，树枝弯曲了，但是没有折断。 3. They refused to bend to the hijackers\' demands. 他们拒绝屈从于劫机者的要求。 4. She can\'t bend him to her will. 她无法使他服从自己的意志。 5. The stream takes a sudden bend to the east. 小溪突然转向东流。', '过去式: bent 过去分词: bent 现在分词: bending 第三人称单数: bends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('seminar', '[\'semɪnɑːr]', 'n.研讨会；(大学的)研究班', '1. The old professor had presided over a seminar for theoretical physicists. 老教授主持了一次理论物理学家的研讨会。 2. I attended almost every lecture and seminar when I was at college. 我上大学时,几乎每一个讲座和研讨会都去参加。 3. He also told me that your attendance at his tutorial and seminar had was poor. 他还告诉我说你的辅导课和讨论课出勤率不高。 4. He conducted a seminar on learning strategies at our campus last weekend. 上周他在我们学校办了一个有关学习策略的学习班。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('humidity', '[hjuː\'mɪdəti]', 'n.湿度；湿气', '1. My laundry will not dry because of the humidity. 由于湿度关系，我的衣物无法晾干。 2. Humidity is a measure of moisture in the atmosphere. 湿度是空气内含水分多少的量度。 3. It\'s said by forecast that the humidity in the air today is 60%. 据预报说今天的空气湿度是百分之六十。 4. Humidity caused me another fit of rheumatism. 湿气使我的风湿病又发作了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('terminal', '[\'tɜːrmɪnl]', 'n.末端；终点站；终点；终端机；航站楼 adj.末端的；终点的；晚期的；（每）学期的', '1. That terminal is live. 那个接头有电。 2. A record message is played when the airport bus approaches the terminal. 当机场班车接近终点时，播放了注意事项录音。 3. I\'ll keep with you to the bus terminal. 我陪你到公共汽车终点站。 4. Please wait for me at the bus terminal. 请在公共汽车终点站等我。 5. Telomere locates on the terminal of DNA containing repeat DNA sequence. 端粒是位于染色体末端的串联重复核苷酸序列。', '副词: terminally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('encounter', '[ɪn\'kaʊntər]', 'n.意外的相见；邂逅；遭遇 v.遭遇；遇到；偶然碰到', '1. If both participate, it may be an actual encounter of bodiless consciousness. 如果是双向的，这会是一个真实的与灵魂的相见。 2. A fortunate encounter brought us together. 一次幸运的邂逅使我们相识。 3. It was a bloody encounter between the two armies. 这是那两军之间的一次激烈的遭遇战。 4. Don\'t be afraid to encounter risks. 不要害怕遭遇危险。', '过去式: encountered 过去分词: encountered 现在分词: encountering 第三人称单数: encounters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('that', '[ðæt]', 'pron.那 conj.引导从句 adj.那个；上文提到的 adv.非常；那么地', '1. What is the difference between this and that? 这个和那个之间的区别是什么？ 2. I walked to the gate that opened towards the lake. 我走向那扇临湖的大门。 3. The output of steel this year has increased by 20% compared with that in 1992. 今年钢产量比一九九二年增长了百分之二十。 4. I am well aware that this is a tough job. 我深知这是一件棘手的工作。 5. That book isn\'t mine. I guess it belongs to Mike. 那本书不是我的，我猜大概是麦克的。 6. Is your problem that complicated? 你的问题非常复杂吗?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('join', '[dʒɔɪn]', 'v.连接；加入；参与；和...一起', '1. The island is joined to the mainland by a bridge. 岛上有座桥与大陆相连。 2. The two estates join at the foot of the hill. 这两处房地产在山脚下相毗连。 3. If you join the club, you must abide by its rules. 你参加这个俱乐部就得遵守其规章。 4. He was asked many times to join the party, but he always kept his distance. 人家好几次要他参加那个政党，但他的反应总是很冷淡。', '过去式: joined 过去分词: joined 现在分词: joining 第三人称单数: joins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feat', '[fiːt]', 'n.技艺；功绩；技艺表演', '1. It was quite a feat to move that piano by yourself. 你真有能耐，一个人挪动那架钢琴。 2. I was amazed to see his dangerous feat. 他的危险技艺让我感到惊讶。 3. The skyscraper is a feat of engineering. 那座摩天大楼是一项工程的壮举。 4. The first flight into space was a brilliant feat. 第一次太空飞行是项光辉的伟绩。', '副词: featly 比较级: feater 最高级: featest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('candidate', '[\'kændɪdət]', 'n.候选人；应试者', '1. There are three candidates for the vacancy. 这一空缺有三名候选人。 2. She had been nominated as candidate for the presidency. 她已被提名为总统候选人。 3. He made several favorable comments about their candidate. 他对他们的候选人发表了一些有利的评论。 4. Most candidates passed in grammar. 参加考试的人大多数语法及格。', '名词: candidacy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('broad', '[brɔːd]', 'adj.宽广的；清楚无误的；明显的；胸怀开阔的；粗俗的 n.<俚>女子', '1. The broad steps in front of the mansion made it look very dignified. 宽阔的台阶使大厦的正面显得很气派。 2. The picture is small but it shows broad vistas. 画幅虽然不大,所表现的天地却十分广阔。 3. The Minister gave a broad hint that she intends to raise taxes. 首相明白地暗示她打算提高税额. 4. The kidnapping occurred in broad daylight. 在光天化日之下竟发生绑架事件。', '副词: broadly 比较级: broader 最高级: broadest 名词: broadness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('leisure', '[\'liːʒər]', 'n.闲暇；休闲', '1. Are you at leisure just now? 你现在有空吗？ 2. Life today is compartmentalized into work and leisure. 现今生活分成工作和闲暇两部分。 3. I have no leisure for playing cards. 我没有闲暇玩牌。 4. He\'s a gentleman of large leisure. 他是一个逍遥自在的绅士。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wall', '[wɔːl]', 'n.墙壁；垣；墙状物 v.围住；隔开；演戏般地转动(眼睛)', '1. The picture on the wall is crooked. 挂在墙壁上的画是歪的。 2. The castle walls are very thick. 城堡的墙很厚。 3. I will break down its wall, and it will be trampled. 我必撤去篱笆，使它被吞灭，拆毁墙垣，使它被践踏。 4. We are going to wall the garden. 我们将要用围墙把花园围起来。', '形容词: wallless 过去式: walled 过去分词: walled 现在分词: walling 第三人称单数: walls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('we', '[wi]', 'pron.我们', '1. We have seen the film. 我们已经看过这部电影。 2. We are fully aware of the gravity of the situation. 我们十分清楚形势的严峻性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('subway', '[\'sʌbweɪ]', 'n.地铁；地下通道', '1. She saw us on the subway. 在地铁站她见到我们了 2. I want to get there by subway. 我想乘地铁去那儿。 3. Last Sunday, a News pressman named Gerald Boyd got worked over with baseball bats on his way to the subway and no one except us gave it much attention. 上星期日，纽约每日新闻一个名字叫波伊德的印刷工人在去地铁途中被人用球棒痛殴。除我们以外没人注意。 4. Use the subway to cross the road. 请走地下通道穿越马路。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('worm', '[wɜːrm]', 'n.虫；蠕虫 v.蠕动；驱虫；慢慢获取', '1. The worm was crushed under the feet. 虫被脚踏扁了。 2. The bird had a worm in its beak. 鸟儿嘴里叼着一条虫。 3. The most infamous is known as the Internet Worm. 其中最臭名昭著的是因特网蠕虫。 4. When you open the file, it activates the worm. 当你一打开文档,就会启动电脑蠕虫。 5. I have no idea as to how to worm out of the job. 我不知如何摆脱这项任务。', '过去式: wormed 过去分词: wormed 现在分词: worming 第三人称单数: worms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('supplement', '[\'sʌplɪmənt]', 'n.增刊；补充物 vt.增补；补充', '1. It comes out each week and it has a magazine supplement. 每周出版一期，还附有杂志增刊。 2. The upset supplement supplier went up with the puppet to the upper room for supper. 心烦意乱的增刊供给者与傀儡一起到上面的房间吃晚餐。 3. The money I got was a useful supplement to my ordinary income. 我得到的那笔钱是很管用的外快。 4. Man\'s work is rather the needful supplement to himself than the outcome of it. 一个人的工作更多地是他自身的必要补充,而非这种补充的结果。 5. She gives private lessons to supplement her income. 她给私人授课以贴补收入。', '形容词: supplementary 名词: supplementarity 过去式: supplemented 过去分词: supplemented 现在分词: supplementing 第三人称单数: supplements');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('timber', '[\'tɪmbər]', 'n.木材；木料', '1. He used to be a timber merchant. 他曾是一个木材商。 2. Seasoned timber does not warp. 经干燥处理的木材不会翘曲。 3. The farmer spent a day in the woods hewing timber. 这个农夫花了一天时间在森林里砍木材。 4. We are making a bed from scrap timber. 我们在用碎木料做一张床。', '过去式: timbered 过去分词: timbered 现在分词: timbering 第三人称单数: timbers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('theory', '[\'θɪri]', 'n.学说；理论；原理；意见', '1. There\'re many theories about the origin of life. 关于生命起源的学说有很多。 2. In theory, anything could happen. 理论上来说,任何事情都会发生。 3. Not everyone can understand Einstein\'s Theory of Relativity. 不是每个人都能读懂爱因斯坦的相对论的。 4. In his book, he explained the operating theories of computer in detail. 在他的书中,他详细阐述了计算机的工作原理。', '名词复数: theories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('telegraph', '[\'telɪɡræf]', 'n.电报；电报机 vt.打电报；显示', '1. It was in an obscure warehouse on Telegraph Road. 那是电报路上一座不明显的仓库。 2. Telegraph to her parents at once. 立即给她父母打电报。 3. Send the message on the telegraph. 这个消息用电报机发出。 4. A teleprinter is really a machine which sends a typewriter message over a telegraph circuit. 打字电报机实际上是一种在电报电路上传送打印信息的机器。', '名词: telegrapher 过去式: telegraphed 过去分词: telegraphed 现在分词: telegraphing 第三人称单数: telegraphs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('birthday', '[\'bɜːrθdeɪ]', 'n.生日', '1. I received a set of gardening tools on my birthday. 生日那天，我收到一套园艺工具。 2. He gave her an expensive fur for her birthday. 他送给她一件昂贵的毛皮衣服作为生日礼物。 3. Tom\'s birthday is this week. 汤姆的生日就在这个星期。 4. Next Monday will be my 21st birthday. 下星期一是我二十一岁的生日。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fridge', '[frɪdʒ]', 'n.电冰箱', '1. She can mend the fridge by herself. 她能自己修理冰箱。 2. The butter will soften out of the fridge. 黄油从冰箱中取出会变软。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cop', '[kɑːp]', 'n.纺锤状线团、管纱；警察 vt.抓住、发现（某人）在干坏事；获得（某事物）、遭受；握住（某物）', '1. Unwinding cop or bad cone into winding suction system 退绕纱管或坏筒子吸入络筒吸纱系统 2. The cop booked John on a charge of speeding. 警察指控约翰超速驾驶。 3. That crazy driver was pulled over by a cop. 那个疯狂的司机被警察拽到了一边。 4. If I cop you cheating again you\'ll be in trouble. 我要再发现你骗人，决不轻饶。', '过去式: copped 过去分词: copped 现在分词: copping 第三人称单数: cops');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('might', '[maɪt]', 'aux.可能；也许；may的过去式 n.威力；力量', '1. That might be in your favor. 那可能对你有利。 2. You might do me a favor? 你或许能帮我—个忙吧? 3. If someone had been with him, he might not have been drowned. 如果有人在他旁边，或许他就不会溺死。 4. The boy might have known the truth, but I am not quite sure. 这男孩当时也许知道真相，但我不很确定。 5. We fear the military might of the enemy. 我们惧怕敌人强大的军事力量。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('free', '[friː]', 'adj.自由的；免费的；畅通的；没有…的；未使用的；空闲的；随意的 v.释放；使自由；使摆脱；解除；使可用于(某目的) adv.免费地；自由地', '1. The prisoners wish to be free again. 囚犯们希望重获自由。 2. As a freelancer, he has more free time to himself. 因为是个自由职业者,他有更多属于自己的自由时间。 3. This service is free of charge. 该服务是免费的。 4. Is the book for free or for a charge? 这本书是免费的,还是收费的? 5. He requested that they free the hostages. 他请求他们释放人质。 6. Children under five usually travel free on trains. 五岁以下的儿童乘火车通常免费。', '副词: freely 比较级: freer 最高级: freest 名词: freeness 过去式: freed 过去分词: freed 现在分词: freeing 第三人称单数: frees');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('morality', '[mə\'ræləti]', 'n.道德；美德；品行；道德观', '1. Have standards of morality improved? 道德标准是否有所改进？ 2. I am unconcerned with questions of religion or morality. 我对宗教问题和道德问题不感兴趣。 3. The crusade for sexual morality is turning into a witch-hunt. 捍卫性道德的运动正在转化成对持异议人士的迫害。 4. The morality they absorbed was beyond question. 他们的美德无可置疑。', '名词复数: moralities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('endeavor', '[ɪn\'devər]', 'n.尽力；努力 v.尽力；努力；力图', '1. Please make every endeavor to be early. 请尽量早点儿。 2. He failed in convincing the buyer despite endeavor. 尽管他已经尽力了,还是无法说服买主。 3. Where there is no hope, there can be no endeavor. 哪里没有希望,哪里就不可能有努力。 4. His success came from endeavor rather than opportunity. 他的成功与其说是由于机遇 5. The man endeavored to please his beloved wife. 那人尽量使他深爱的妻子快乐。', '名词: endeavorer 过去式: endeavored 过去分词: endeavored 现在分词: endeavoring 第三人称单数: endeavors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('subtract', '[səb\'trækt]', 'vt.减去 vi.减少', '1. If you subtract 2 from 8, you get 6. 8减去2是6。 2. Please subtract a quarter of the money for your own use. 请扣除四分之一的钱由你自己支配使用。 3. The little girl has begin to learn to add and subtract. 这小女孩已在学做加减法了。', '名词: subtracter 过去式: subtracted 过去分词: subtracted 现在分词: subtracting 第三人称单数: subtracts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('privacy', '[\'praɪvəsi]', 'n.隐居；隐私；秘密；私生活', '1. Everyone has his own privacy. 每个人都有自己的隐私。 2. I object to our privacy being invaded. 我反对我们的隐私权受到侵害。 3. He was sentenced to be guilty of intrusion upon my privacy. 他因侵犯我的隐私权被判有罪。 4. I tell you this in strict privacy. 我极秘密地告诉你这件事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('break', '[breɪk]', 'v.打碎；折断；违背；解决；中断；透露；变弱；锐减；结束 n.破裂；休息；中断；急冲；好运', '1. If you discover a fire, break the glass to sound the fire alarm. 如果你发现了火灾,打碎玻璃去弄响火警铃报警。 2. To frighten the dog, he broke a twig from the tree. 为了吓唬那只狗,他从树上折了一根小树枝。 3. What shocked the workers was that the boss had broken his promise. 工人们感到震惊的是,老板竟然违背了诺言。 4. The spy had finally broken the code. 那个间谍最终破译了密码。 5. A break in the pipe was found out. 管道上有一处裂缝。', '过去式: broke 过去分词: broken 现在分词: breaking 第三人称单数: breaks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('study', '[\'stʌdi]', 'n.研究；学习；学科；书房；(绘画或文学)习作；练习曲；沉思；记忆力…的人；台词记得…的人 v.研究；学习；读书；仔细观察；努力', '1. This reference book is very useful to our study. 这本参考书对我们的研究很有用。 2. He persisted in the study of law. 他坚持学习法律。 3. His years of study were useful in his job. 他多年的学习有助于他的工作。 4. Physiology is the study of how living things work. 生理学是研究生物功能的学科。 5. Scientists are studying the photographs of Mars for signs of life. 科学家们正在研究火星的照片，寻求生命的迹象。', '名词复数: studies 过去式: studied 过去分词: studied 现在分词: studying 第三人称单数: studies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('period', '[\'pɪriəd]', 'n.一段时间；周期；时期；课时；学时；句号；月经', '1. He feels completely restored to health after a period of intensive care. 通过一段时间的精心照顾，他感到身体完全康复了。 2. The exercise period was similar to the previous study. 运动周期类似前面的研究。 3. Childhood is a period of rapid growth. 幼年是生长迅速的时期。 4. He teaches 10 periods a week. 他每周授课10课时。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cabbage', '[\'kæbɪdʒ]', 'n.卷心菜；洋白菜', '1. He is busy pricking out some cabbage seedlings. 他正忙于移植一些卷心菜秧。 2. Cabbage could be eaten raw in salads. 卷心菜可以做成沙拉生吃。 3. I like to cook dishes with cabbage. 我喜欢用洋白菜做菜。 4. The cabbage germinated within a week. 白菜一星期内就发芽了。', '形容词: cabbagy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('epidemic', '[ˌepɪ\'demɪk]', 'n.流行病；传染病 adj.流行的；传染性的', '1. A flu epidemic raged through the school for weeks. 流感在这所学校里蔓延了几个星期。 2. The small town was suddenly struck by an epidemic. 小镇突然遭到传染病的袭击。 3. Violence is reaching epidemic levels. 暴力达到了流行的程度。 4. The corruption has become epidemic in the society. 这种腐化已成为社会上的一种歪风。', '副词: epidemically 异体字: epidemical');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('propose', '[prə\'poʊz]', 'v.打算；计划；向 ... 提议；求婚；提名', '1. I propose an early start tomorrow morning. 我打算明天早上早点出发。 2. He proposed to buy and run a farm. 他计划购买并经营一个农场。 3. The committee proposed that new legislation should be drafted. 委员会建议着手起草新法规。 4. He had proposed marriage, unsuccessfully, twice already. 他已经两次求婚，均未成功。', '名词: proposer 过去式: proposed 过去分词: proposed 现在分词: proposing 第三人称单数: proposes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drought', '[draʊt]', 'n.干旱', '1. The long drought famished many people. 久旱使很多人陷入饥饿。 2. Famine is often the sequel to war or drought. 饥荒往往是战争或干旱造成的。 3. We have not enough food to eat because of the drought. 因为旱灾，我们没有足够的食物可吃。 4. The soil is cracking up because of the drought. 土地因干旱而正在龟裂。', '形容词: droughty 异体字: drouth');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('practice', '[\'præktɪs]', 'n.练习；实行；习惯；业务 v.练习；实践；开业；执业', '1. Daily practice is the trick in learning a foreign language. 每天练习是学会一门外语的诀窍。 2. We must put our plans into practice. 我们必须将计划付诸实行。 3. You should make a practice of being on time for work. 你应该养成准时上班的习惯。 4. I have a culture and art practice in my company. 我公司开办一项文化和艺术业务。', '名词: practicer 过去式: practiced 过去分词: practiced 现在分词: practicing 第三人称单数: practices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('meat', '[miːt]', 'n.肉；主要或重要部分', '1. The meat will rot if it isn\'t kept cool. 肉如果不冷藏就会腐败。 2. She gave some of the meat to the cat. 她把一些肉给猫吃了。 3. There\'s not much meat on that bone. 那块骨头上没多少肉。 4. The meat will scorch if you don\'t lower the gas. 如果你不把煤气调小一点，肉就要焦了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brilliant', '[\'brɪljənt]', 'adj.卓越的；灿烂的；美妙的；杰出的；才华横溢的 n.宝石', '1. He has got brilliant achievements in the field of physics. 他在物理学方面已经取得了卓越的成就。 2. The brilliant sun lit up their rooms. 灿烂的阳光照亮了他们的屋子。 3. Memory is like a living book whose brilliant fragments worth reading a hundred times in my life. 回忆就像是一本生动的书,生活中那些精彩的片段令我百读不厌。 4. The novel is considered a brilliant performance. 这部小说被认为是出色的佳作。', '副词: brilliantly 名词: brilliantness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('delicious', '[dɪ\'lɪʃəs]', 'adj.美味的；可口的', '1. She can produce delicious meal from very simple ingredients. 她能用简单配料烹调出美味的饭菜。 2. The hunter entertained us with venison which was very delicious. 猎人拿出了非常美味的鹿肉招待我们。 3. The bannock is delicious. 这种薄饼很可口。 4. I like the delicious salad of crisp lettuce and tomatos. 我喜欢这种脆莴苣和番茄做的沙拉，很好吃。', '副词: deliciously 名词: deliciousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('description', '[dɪ\'skrɪpʃn]', 'n.描述；刻画；类型；说明书', '1. He gave a description of what he had seen. 他描述了他所见到的一切。 2. The scenery is beautiful beyond descriptions. 那风景美丽得难以形容。 3. He is very good at the description about the characters of different figures in his book. 他非常擅长在书中刻画不同人物的性格。 4. There are boats of every description on the lake. 湖上漂着各种类型的船。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mistake', '[mɪ\'steɪk]', 'n.错误；误会；过失 v.误解；弄错', '1. His costly mistake resulted in severe loss. 他的严重的错误导致了重大的损失。 2. You\'ve made several grammatical mistakes in the composition. 你的作文中犯了几处语法错误。 3. Tom must have taken your dictionary by mistake. 汤姆一定是弄错了才拿了你的字典。 4. He felt mortified for his mistake. 他对自己的过失深感羞愧。 5. You mistook my meaning entirely. 你完全误解了我的意思。', '名词: mistaker 过去式: mistook 过去分词: mistaken 现在分词: mistaking 第三人称单数: mistakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('league', '[liːɡ]', 'n.种类；社团；联盟；同盟；里格（长度单位，约为3英里或3海里） v.（使）结盟', '1. They are not in the same league. 他们的水平有高低。 2. Our club is a member of the Football League. 我们的俱乐部是足球联合会的一员。 3. Most of us in our class are League members. 我们班上大多数是团员。 4. He is a member of the Ivy League. 他是长春藤联合会的一员。 5. We must league together against this threat. 面对这种威胁我们必须联合起来。', '过去式: leagued 过去分词: leagued 现在分词: leaguing 第三人称单数: leagues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dumb', '[dʌm]', 'adj.哑的；愚蠢的；不能说话的 vt.使沉默', '1. She\'s been dumb from birth. 她生来就是哑巴。 2. It was dumb of you to say that. 你说那种话真是太愚蠢了。 3. She was unfairly caricatured as a dumb blonde. 她被不公正地丑化成了一个傻头傻脑的金发女郎。 4. He was struck dumb by her sharp question. 他被她那尖锐的问题弄得哑口无言。', '副词: dumbly 比较级: dumber 最高级: dumbest 名词: dumbness 过去式: dumbed 过去分词: dumbed 现在分词: dumbing 第三人称单数: dumbs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('way', '[weɪ]', 'n.路；路线；方法；方式；作风；样子；方向；出入通道；距离；时间段；地区；方面；情况 adv.非常；远远地 adj.途中的，中途的', '1. I am on my way to the grocery store. 我正在去杂货店的路上。 2. We lost the way in the dark. 我们在黑夜中迷路了。 3. He asked me the way to London. 他问我去伦敦的路。 4. He tried in every way to verify this theory. 他想一切办法来验证这个理论。 5. It seems like I\'m always way too busy with work. 我工作总是太忙了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evoke', '[ɪ\'voʊk]', 'vt.唤起；引起', '1. Songs can evoke old memories. 歌曲可以唤起往日的回忆。 2. Pieces of fine art may evoke emotional or spiritual responses in us. 一件件精美的艺术品可以唤起我们情感和精神上的响应。 3. The photographs evoked strong memories of our holidays in France. 照片唤起了我们在法国度假的深深的记忆。 4. His case is unlikely to evoke public sympathy. 他的情况不大可能引起公众的同情。', '形容词: evocable 过去式: evoked 过去分词: evoked 现在分词: evoking 第三人称单数: evokes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('species', '[\'spiːʃiːz]', 'n.种类；（单复同）物种', '1. He is wearing a strange species of hat. 他戴着一种奇怪的帽子。 2. There are more than 1,000 alien species in China. 中国的外来物种有1000多种。 3. The giant panda has become an endangered species. 大熊猫已成了一种濒临灭绝的动物。 4. There has been a sharp decline in the number of species. 物种数量骤然下降。', '名词复数: species');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('injury', '[\'ɪndʒəri]', 'n.伤害；损害', '1. She still suffers considerable discomfort from her injury. 她因那次受伤至今仍感不适。 2. He had a spinal injury in that accident. 他在那次事故中脊柱受了伤。 3. The injury to their key player could be a decisive factor in the game. 他们主力队员受伤可能是这场比赛胜负的决定性因素。 4. Motorcyclists must wear helmets to shield them from injury. 摩托车手必须戴头盔保护自己免受伤害。', '名词复数: injuries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('demonstrate', '[\'demənstreɪt]', 'vt.证明；演示；示范 vi.示威', '1. How can you demonstrate to us that your story is true? 你怎样才能向我们证明你所说的属实呢? 2. Realized benefits demonstrate good practice. 已实现的利益证明好的实践。 3. You have to demonstrate how to operate the computer. 你得演示一下如何使用这台计算机。 4. The students are demonstrating a chemical law in the laboratory. 学生们正在实验室里演示一条化学定理。 5. The workers marched through the streets with flags and banners to demonstrate against the rising cost of living . 工人们在街上游行，手执旗帜示威抗议生活费用的高涨。', '过去式: demonstrated 过去分词: demonstrated 现在分词: demonstrating 第三人称单数: demonstrates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jet', '[dʒet]', 'n.喷气式飞机；喷口；喷射；喷气式发动机 v.喷射；喷出；搭乘喷射式飞机', '1. Developing the supersonic jet was quite an accomplishment. 开发超音速喷气机是一项了不起的成就。 2. The accident happened as the jet was about to take off. 喷气式飞机正要起飞时出了事故。 3. He left on the jet plane. 他坐飞机离开了。 4. Clean the gas jets on the cooker. 把煤气炉的喷口弄干净。 5. The water jetted out. 一股水喷涌而出。', '名词: jetful 过去式: jetted 过去分词: jetted 现在分词: jetting 第三人称单数: jets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('uniform', '[\'juːnɪfɔːrm]', 'n.制服 adj.一致的；统一的', '1. He looks very manly in his uniform. 他穿着制服十分精神。 2. The students are wearing school uniforms. 学生们穿着校服。 3. The rows of houses were uniform in appearance. 这一排排的房屋外表都是一样的。 4. Their internal temperatures are essentially uniform with the environment. 它们的体温与周围环境基本上是一致的。', '副词: uniformly 名词: uniformity 过去式: uniformed 过去分词: uniformed 现在分词: uniforming 第三人称单数: uniforms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grand', '[ɡrænd]', 'adj.重大的；豪华的；宏伟的；壮丽的 n.大钢琴；一千美元', '1. This is a grand occasion. 这是个盛大的场面。 2. He was born in the purple and was brought up in the grand palace. 他出身于皇族,在宏伟的宫殿中长大。 3. How grand the mountains look in the early evening! 暮色中群山是多么壮丽！ 4. The piano soon developed into the contemporary nine- to ten-foot concert grand. 不久钢琴就发展到同时代的九到十英尺的平台大钢琴。', '副词: grandly 比较级: grander 最高级: grandest 名词: grandness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strip', '[strɪp]', 'v.剥去；剥夺；脱衣；除去 n.脱衣舞；长条；条状', '1. Elephants strip the leaves from trees. 大象剥去了树上的叶子。 2. It was wrong of him to strip his daughter of the right to education. 他不该剥夺他女儿受教育的权利。 3. Having been stripped of all his titles, he disappeared from public life. 他被剥夺一切荣誉之后，就从公共生活中消声匿迹了。 4. The children stripped off their clothes and jumped into the river. 孩子们脱掉衣服跳进河里。 5. You met me at a strip club. 你和我是在脱衣舞俱乐部里认识的。', '过去式: stripped 过去分词: stripped 现在分词: stripping 第三人称单数: strips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ridiculous', '[rɪ\'dɪkjələs]', 'adj.荒谬的；可笑的', '1. His social pretensions make him appear ridiculous. 他冒充上流社会人士而出尽洋相。 2. His aristocratic manners seemed ridiculous in this poor area. 在这个贫穷的地区，他的贵族气派显得很可笑。 3. I\'ll show you how to settle such ridiculous stuff. 你瞧我怎样来对付这种无稽之谈。 4. That\'s ridiculous. 那太荒唐了。', '副词: ridiculously 名词: ridiculousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('zoom', '[zuːm]', 'v.急速上升；嗡嗡作响；（镜头）拉近（拉远） n.急速上升；嗡嗡声；(摄影)变焦', '1. Overnight trading caused share prices to zoom up. 一夜的交投使股票价格直线上升。 2. We heard a jet plane zooming overhead. 我们听见喷射机在头上嗡嗡作响。 3. If you zoom out at this point, we shall get a view of the whole square. 如果你在此地把镜头推远，我们将看到整个广场。 4. The airplane\' s zoom carried it above the clouds. 飞机的陡直上升使它飞到云层之上。', '过去式: zoomed 过去分词: zoomed 现在分词: zooming 第三人称单数: zooms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('locality', '[loʊ\'kæləti]', 'n.地区；位置；地点；方位', '1. There are several supermarkets in the locality. 这个地区有好几家超市。 2. Public transport is a big problem in this locality. 公共交通是这个地区的大问题。 3. People in this locality used to take two meals a day. 这儿的居民过去每天吃两餐饭。 4. They are trying to pinpoint the ship\'s exact locality. 他们正在设法确定轮船的确切位置。', '名词复数: localities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('permanent', '[\'pɜːrmənənt]', 'adj.永久的；持久的 n.<口> 烫发', '1. The incident left permanent traces on his mind. 那件事在他头脑里留下了永久的印象。 2. I am looking for a permanent position. 我在找一个永久性的职业。 3. These factors usually have a longer and more permanent impact on share prices. 这项因素通常会对股价产生更加长远和持久的影响。', '副词: permanently 名词: permanentness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mud', '[mʌd]', 'n.泥；泥浆；诽谤 vt.弄脏；抹泥', '1. My car\'s stuck in the mud, and it won\'t budge. 我的车陷入泥中，一动也不动。 2. He removed the mud from his shoes. 他去掉鞋上的泥。 3. As the bus passed, it spattered mud on my clothes. 公共汽车开过时溅了我一身泥。 4. The heavy wheels churned the earth into mud. 笨重的车轮将大地碾成了泥浆。 5. His clothes were daubed with mud. 他的衣服被泥浆弄脏了。', '过去式: mudded 过去分词: mudded 现在分词: mudding 第三人称单数: muds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('always', '[\'ɔːlweɪz]', 'adv.总是；一直；始终；永远；随时；无论如何', '1. I\'m always at home in the evenings. 晚上我总是在家里。 2. A live band is always a good draw at a party. 现场演奏的乐队在聚会上总是很吸引人的。 3. We should always help each other. 我们应始终互相帮助。 4. They will always be friends. 他们将永远是朋友。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('escalate', '[\'eskəleɪt]', 'vt.升级 vi.升高；逐步升级', '1. Shouting may seem necessary, but it tends to escalate conflicts. 大喊大叫也许比较容易，但是它容易导致使冲突升级。 2. The government is deliberately escalating the war for political reasons. 政府出于政治目的蓄意使战争逐步升级。 3. House prices have escalated rapidly. 房价已急速上涨。 4. Even a limited confrontation can escalate into a major war. 即使是局部的对抗也可能扩大成一场大战。', '形容词: escalatory 名词: escalation 过去式: escalated 过去分词: escalated 现在分词: escalating 第三人称单数: escalates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('station', '[\'steɪʃn]', 'n.站；火车站；电视台；社会地位；牧羊场；驻地；岗位 v.驻扎；安置', '1. Don\'t forget to drop by at the gas station. 别忘了到煤气站去看看。 2. He was walking up and down the station platform. 他在火车站的月台上走来走去。 3. Can you tell me the way to the railway station? 你能告诉我往火车站的路怎么走吗？ 4. Which TV station is the programme on? 这个节目在哪家电视台播放? 5. Guards were stationed around the prison. 卫兵派驻在监狱四周。', '过去式: stationed 过去分词: stationed 现在分词: stationing 第三人称单数: stations');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wonder', '[\'wʌndər]', 'n.惊奇；惊愕；奇迹；奇观 v.惊奇；想知道；怀疑 adj.奇妙的；非凡的', '1. There was a look of wonder in his eyes. 他眼中露出惊奇的神色。 2. They were filled with wonder at the new waterfall. 他们对新瀑布感到非常惊奇。 3. Colour television is realty a wonder. 彩色电视真是一个奇迹。 4. It\'s a wonder that the child came through without a scratch. 这孩子竟能安然无恙地脱险，真是奇迹。 5. I shouldn\'t wonder if he wins the prize. 如果他获奖，我不会感到惊奇。 6. We have become explorers and scientists with our need to ask questions and to wonder. 为了解答疑问和探索奇妙的自然，我们成为探险家和科学家。', '名词: wonderer 过去式: wondered 过去分词: wondered 现在分词: wondering 第三人称单数: wonders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ever', '[\'evər]', 'adv.曾经；在任何时候；究竟；一直；永远', '1. I don\'t think I ever met you. 我觉得我没见过你。 2. Have you ever been to Beijing? 你去过北京吗? 3. Nothing ever happens in this village. 这村里从来没有发生过什么事情。 4. Who ever can it be? 那究竟会是谁呢?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jewelry', '[\'dʒuːəlrɪ]', 'n.珠宝；珠宝类', '1. This is a case with separate compartments for shoes, jewelry, etc. 这是一个分格存放鞋、珠宝等的箱子。 2. Jewelry and lace are mostly feminine belongings. 珠宝和蕾丝大多是女性用品。 3. I bought the watch at the jewelry counter. 这只表是我在珠宝柜买的。 4. The gang knocked over a jewelry store. 这伙歹徒抢劫了一家珠宝店。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dispute', '[dɪ\'spjuːt]', 'v.争论；辩驳；争议；质疑 n.争论；争端；争吵', '1. The couple disputed where to spend the holiday. 夫妻俩为上哪儿度假而发生争论。 2. It is ridiculous to dispute about such a thing. 为这样的事情而争论简直荒谬可笑。 3. \"I\'m not disputing what you say, matt.\" said Tremaine, shaking his head. “我并不是要跟你辩驳，麦特”，屈里曼说，摇摇头。 4. Now there was just one point on the boundary left to dispute. 边界上有一点引起争议。 5. A long dispute means that both parties are wrong.( Voltaire) 持久的争论意味着双方都是错的。(伏尔泰)', '名词: disputer 过去式: disputed 过去分词: disputed 现在分词: disputing 第三人称单数: disputes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lottery', '[\'lɑːtəri]', 'n.彩票', '1. We freaked out when we won the lottery. 中了奖券,我们兴奋极了。 2. Congratulations on winning the lottery. 恭喜你中了彩票。', '名词复数: lotteries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('creature', '[\'kriːtʃər]', 'n.生物；动物；人', '1. This creature lives in the depth of the ocean. 这种生物生活在海洋深处。 2. We can\'t see microscopic creature with naked eyes. 我们不能用肉眼看到微生物。 3. Pandas are precious creatures. 熊猫是珍贵的动物。 4. The old lady is such a dear creature. 这位老太太是位非常可爱的人。', '形容词: creatural 名词: creatureliness 名词复数: creatures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('figure', '[\'fɪɡjər]', 'n.图形；数字；外形；体型；形状；人物；塑像；图表；（冰上表演动作的）花样 v.是重要部分；认为；演算；领会到', '1. Our textbook has many figures to help explain the lessons. 我们的教科书有许多图表帮助解释课文。 2. The figure is expressed as a percentage. 那数字是以百分比表示的。 3. He has a more angular figure than his father. 他的体型比他的父亲更显得有棱角。 4. I like the color of the hat instead of its figure. 虽然我喜欢这顶帽子的颜色,但我不喜欢它的形状。 5. My feelings about the matter didn\'t seem to figure at all. 我对这个问题的意见似乎根本无足轻重。', '名词: figurer 过去式: figured 过去分词: figured 现在分词: figuring 第三人称单数: figures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('necklace', '[\'nekləs]', 'n.项链', '1. I value this necklace at $5,000. 我估计这条项链值五千美元。 2. The girl is wearing a bead necklace. 女孩戴了一条珠子项链。', '名词复数: necklaces 过去式: necklaced 过去分词: necklaced');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('independence', '[ˌɪndɪ\'pendəns]', 'n.独立；自立', '1. The country attained its independence in 1972. 这个国家在1972年获得了独立。 2. The government adopted an uncompromising posture on the issue of independence. 政府在独立的问题上采取了毫不妥协的态度。 3. I tried to preserve my independence. 我试图保持自己的独立性。 4. This money gives me independence from my family. 这笔钱使我能离家自立了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('marital', '[\'mærɪtl]', 'adj.婚姻的', '1. We don\'t know her marital status, whether or not she has children. 我们不清楚她的婚姻状况,也不知道她是否有孩子。 2. We can define marital felicity accurately. 我们能够给美满婚姻下个准确定义。 3. He is faced with the fact of an irremediable marital breakdown. 他面临着不可挽救的婚姻破裂的事实。 4. He did not appear to have any financial or marital problems. 他看起来没有任何经济或婚姻问题。', '副词: maritally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('practical', '[\'præktɪkl]', 'adj.明智的；实际的；实用的；事实上的 n.实践考试', '1. A practical person does not spend his money and time foolishly. 一个有头脑的人是不胡乱花钱和虚度光阴的。 2. It\'s an interesting idea, but there are many practical difficulties. 这是一个很有意思的想法,然而却存在着许多实际困难。 3. Most importantly, we should develop our own practical ability. 最重要的是,我们应该提高自身的实践能力。 4. Your invention is not practical. 你的发明不实用。 5. His practical at the hospital went well enough. 他在医院的实习进行得相当好。', '名词: practicality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heighten', '[\'haɪtn]', 'v.增加；升高；加强', '1. A weakened immune system does not heighten the risks of catching a cold. 一个弱免疫系统是不会增加感冒的感染可能性的。 2. An older more experienced swimmer will shave his entire body to reduce resistance and heighten sensation in the water. 年龄较大更有经验的游泳运动员将会把他的全身收紧以减少阻力并增加水感。 3. The financial management must be strengthened so as to heighten economic profits. 要提高经济效益，必须加强财务管理。 4. So it is urgent for curriculum reform to reinforce teachers\' team building and heighten the integrated quality of teachers. 加强教师队伍建设，提高教师的整体素质，是新课程改革的迫切要求。', '名词: heightener 过去式: heightened 过去分词: heightened 现在分词: heightening 第三人称单数: heightens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sweep', '[swiːp]', 'v.打扫；掠过；扫视；席卷；全胜；清除 n.清扫；连绵一片；席卷；掠过；范围；搜寻；(竞赛中)全胜；赌金', '1. He picked up the broom to help me sweep the floor. 他拿起扫帚帮我扫地。 2. They asked the little boy to sweep the room clean. 他们叫那个小男孩把房间打扫干净。 3. His fingers swept the keys of the piano. 他的手指在钢琴键盘上轻快地移动。 4. The breeze sweeps the crystal mirror of the pool. 微风掠过清如明鉴的一泓池水。 5. This floor needs a good sweep. 这地板需要好好清扫一下。', '名词: sweeper 过去式: swept 过去分词: swept 现在分词: sweeping 第三人称单数: sweeps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('buffet', '[bə\'feɪ]', 'n.自助餐；饮食柜台；打击 vt.连续猛击；打击', '1. We serve buffet during lunchtime only. 我们只在午餐时间供应自助餐。 2. We had a buffet supper last evening. 昨天晚上，我们吃了一次自助晚餐。 3. In the corner of the room there was a small buffet. 在屋子角落里有一小的餐具柜。 4. There was a caterers\' buffet stretching all around the dining room. 餐厅周围有一排饮食承办者的冷餐台。 5. Strong winds buffet the ship from time to time. 狂风时不时地击打着航船。', '名词: buffeter 过去式: buffeted 过去分词: buffeted 现在分词: buffeting 第三人称单数: buffets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('molecule', '[\'mɑːlɪkjuːl]', 'n.分子；微粒', '1. A molecule is made up of atoms. 分子由原子组成。 2. Two atoms of hydrogen combine with one atom of oxygen to form a molecule of water. 两个氢原子和一个氧原子结合而成一个水分子。 3. We can see many molecules flying in the air when a sunbeam penetrated the dark room. 当一束光线穿进暗淡的房间时，我们可以看到空气中有许多小颗粒在飞舞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('patch', '[pætʃ]', 'n.小片；补丁；眼罩；（贴在伤口的）膏药；【生态】斑块 vt.修补；补缀；解决；掩饰', '1. The ground is wet in patches. 地上湿处片片。 2. He reset a patch of land with tomato plants. 他在一小块地上重新种上番茄。 3. She sewed a patch onto the knee of the trousers. 她在裤子的膝部打了个补丁. 4. He would indeed seek to patch things up. 他一定会设法把事情加以补救。', '形容词: patchable 名词: patcher 过去式: patched 过去分词: patched 现在分词: patching 第三人称单数: patches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('occasion', '[ə\'keɪʒn]', 'n.场合；时机；理由；机会；盛大场面 vt.引起；致使', '1. I only wear a tie on special occasions. 我只在特殊场合才打领带。 2. This is not an occasion for laughter. 这不是笑的时候. 3. There was no occasion for you to be so rude. 你没有理由这样粗鲁。 4. This will be an occasion for us all to make a new start. 这是我们大家重新开始的好机会。 5. What occasioned his angry protest is the rival\'s deliberate and cynical foul. 对手的恶意犯规引起他的愤怒反抗。', '过去式: occasioned 过去分词: occasioned 现在分词: occasioning 第三人称单数: occasions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('concentration', '[ˌkɒnsen\'treɪʃən]', 'n.集中；专心；浓度', '1. The tennis players need total concentration during play. 网球运动员在比赛中需要全神贯注。 2. Stress and tiredness often result in a lack of concentration. 紧张和疲劳常使人精神不集中。 3. Concentration is essential if you want to do a good job. 如果你想把事情做好,专心是必要的。 4. His area of concentration is economics. 他专心研究经济学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('voltage', '[\'voʊltɪdʒ]', 'n.电压', '1. Its voltage has not been exceeded. 它的电压没有超过。 2. It is fed into the grid at this voltage. 它是以这种电压馈入电力网。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fresh', '[freʃ]', 'adj.新鲜的；清新的；新近的；无经验的 adv.最近地', '1. Some tribes migrate with their cattle in search of fresh grass. 有些部落为了寻找新鲜的牧草而带着他们的牲畜迁移。 2. Open the window and let in some fresh air. 打开窗户，让新鲜的空气进来。 3. When fresh supplies come into the market, we can revert to your enquiry. 等新货上市时，我们才能回头考虑你们的询盘。 4. I feel really fresh after my holiday. 我度假之後真觉得又精神饱满了。', '副词: freshly 比较级: fresher 最高级: freshest 名词: freshness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('propel', '[prə\'pel]', 'v.推进；驱使', '1. He used a paddle to propel the boat. 他用船桨将船推进。 2. The proper use of imagination can then propel ideas in the directions you desire. 适当运用想象力可以将思想往你所希望的方向推进。', '过去式: propelled 过去分词: propelled 现在分词: propelling 第三人称单数: propels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nobody', '[\'noʊbədi]', 'n.无足轻重的人；小人物 pron.没有人', '1. She has almost nobody to take up for her. 她几乎没有人支持。 2. Nobody likes to live in that desert region. 没有人喜欢生活在那个沙漠地区。', '名词复数: nobodies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conversion', '[kən\'vɜːrʒn]', 'n.转变；换算', '1. He has undergone a religious conversion. 经历一次宗教信仰的转变。 2. In the conversion of saliva into poison, one might suppose that a fixed process took place. 人们可能认为,唾液转变成毒液,其中有固定的程序。 3. When he saw how the theory increased unemployment, he underwent quite a conversion. 当他看到这个理论加重了失业后，他彻底改变了看法。 4. Conversion to gas central heating will save you a lot of money. 改用煤气集中供暖将节省大笔开支。', '形容词: conversional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('high', '[haɪ]', 'adj.高的；高尚的；高级的；高度的；全盛的 adv.高；奢侈地；音调高 n.高水平；高气压；（麻醉品带来的）快感', '1. He earned a high reputation for his learning. 他在学识方面享有很高的声誉。 2. It\'s unsafe to sit the child in such a high chair. 让小孩坐在这么高的椅子上不安全。 3. My grandma was a woman of high principles. 我祖母是一位道德高尚的人。 4. He is a high official in the government. 他是政府的高级官员。 5. The plane flew high above. 飞机高高地在上空飞。 6. Grain output reached a new high in the three years. 谷物产量达到三年中最高水平。', '副词: highly 比较级: higher 最高级: highest');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mind', '[maɪnd]', 'n.头脑；精神；心；想法；意见；心思；注意力；有才智的人；记忆；心情；理智；[宗]追思弥撒；上帝 v.留心；注意；专心于；介意；照顾', '1. He is ninety years old,but his mind is sharp. 他虽然90岁了,但头脑还很灵活。 2. Her death had an unbalancing effect on Joe\'s mind. 她一死,乔在精神上打击很大。 3. I tried to fix the date in my mind. 我试着把那个日期牢记在心。 4. Despite what she says, I won\'t change my mind. 不管她怎么说,我都不会改变我的想法的。 5. Mind the dog! It may be fierce. 留神那条狗! 可能很凶。', '名词: minder 过去式: minded 过去分词: minded 现在分词: minding 第三人称单数: minds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('belief', '[bɪ\'liːf]', 'n.信念；信仰；相信', '1. It bolstered my belief. 这增强了我的信念。 2. He acted in accordance with his beliefs. 他按照自己的信念行事。 3. His belief of communism is immovable. 他坚定不移地信仰共产主义。 4. His firmness on his belief supported him in difficulties. 困境中，他坚定的信仰支撑着他。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overnight', '[ˌoʊvər\'naɪt]', 'adv.在夜里；过夜；突然 adj.整晚的；很快的', '1. The wind had strengthened overnight. 夜里，风更大了。 2. The city was conquered overnight. 那座城市在夜里被攻克。 3. They kept her in hospital overnight. 他们留她在医院过夜。 4. I stayed overnight at a friend\'s house. 我在朋友家过了一夜。 5. Overnight rain will end by morning. 下了整晚的雨会在早上停止。', '过去式: overnighted 过去分词: overnighted 现在分词: overnighting 第三人称单数: overnights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('notwithstanding', '[ˌnɑːtwɪθ\'stændɪŋ]', 'adv.虽然；尽管 prep.纵使 conj.虽然', '1. He went, notwithstanding he was ordered to stay. 他虽被命令不许去，但还是去了。 2. Notwithstanding her naughtiness, I love my little girl. 尽管我的小姑娘很淘气，我还是很爱她。 3. Notwithstanding the bad weather, the match went on. 尽管天气很糟，比赛还是照常进行。 4. He still went home, notwithstanding the midnight. 尽管已近午夜，他还是回家去了。 5. Many people told me not to try, but I went ahead notwithstanding. 很多人都劝我不要尝试,我还是决意去做了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dwarf', '[dwɔːrf]', 'n.矮子；侏儒 vt.使矮小 vi.变小', '1. You are a giant of words and dwarf of action. 你是言词的巨人,行动的矮子。 2. There is a dwarf apple tree in our garden. 在我们的花园里有一棵矮苹果树。 3. The kind dwarf asked the little princess to have dinner with him. 善良的小矮人邀请小公主和他一起吃晚饭。 4. A dwarf on a giant\'s shoulders sees further of the two. 侏儒站在巨人肩上要比两个人看得远。 5. Each innovation destined to dwarf the extensive accomplishment of the Greeks-Euclidean geometry. 每一个创新都注定希腊人的巨大成就--欧几里德几何相形见绌。 6. They act out their dramas in a setting whose wilderness immensity both dwarf and ennobles whatever they achieve 他们在荒原上奠定了他们的事业，而广阔无际的天地既使他们的成就显得渺小，也显得崇高。', '形容词: dwarfish 名词: dwarfishness 名词复数: dwarfs 过去式: dwarfed 过去分词: dwarfed 现在分词: dwarfing 第三人称单数: dwarfs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nourish', '[\'nɜːrɪʃ]', 'v.滋养；给营养；培育；怀有', '1. They needed good food to nourish their bodies. 他们需要好食品滋养身体。 2. Milk is all we need to nourish a small baby. 我们供给婴儿营养只需喂奶就够了。 3. Most plants are nourished by water drawn up through their roots. 多数植物是靠着根吸收水分来维持生命的。 4. The school\'s goal is to nourish young musical talent. 这个学校的目标是培育年轻的音乐人才。', '名词: nourisher 过去式: nourished 过去分词: nourished 现在分词: nourishing 第三人称单数: nourishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('definition', '[ˌdefɪ\'nɪʃn]', 'n.定义；阐释；清晰度', '1. To give a definition of a word is more difficult than to give an illustration of its use. 给一个词下定义要比举例说明它的用法困难。 2. My duties require clearer definition. 我的职责需要更清楚的说明。 3. The photo lacks definition. 这张照片不够清晰。', '形容词: definitional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('product', '[\'prɑːdʌkt]', 'n.产品；产物；结果；某种影响下产生的人或物；乘积', '1. If our product is properly marketed, it shall sell very well. 如果我们的产品适当加以推销,销路应该很好。 2. The hand is not only the organ of labour, it is also the product of labour. 手不仅是劳动的器官,它还是劳动的产物。 3. The eastern frontier of France was the product of centuries of historical accidents. 法国东部的边境是百年来历史上风云变幻的结果。 4. They are the products of post-war affluence. 他们是战後富裕生活的产儿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('treason', '[\'triːzn]', 'n.叛逆 通敌 背叛 叛国罪', '1. He was executed for treason. 他因叛国罪已处死。 2. He was beheaded for high treason. 他因叛国罪被斩首。 3. English politician and historian who was falsely accused of treason and banished(1667). While in France he wrote his major work, The History of the Rebellion and Civil Wars in England(1702-1704). 克拉伦登英国政治家和历史学家，被错判叛国罪并流放(1667年)。在法国写出他的重要著作英国叛乱和内战史(1702－1704年) 4. They have committed treason against the state. 他们已犯了叛国罪。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('behave', '[bɪ\'heɪv]', 'v.表现；行为；举止', '1. How is your new car behaving? 你的新车性能如何？ 2. I\'ll trust you to behave responsibly while I\'m out. 我相信你在我外出期间会认真办事的。 3. If you behave like that, you\'ll get yourself disliked. 如果你的行为那样，你会让人厌恶的。 4. It\'s hard to train children to behave well at the table. 培养儿童用餐时举止得体是很困难的。', '过去式: behaved 过去分词: behaved 现在分词: behaving 第三人称单数: behaves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('noun', '[naʊn]', 'n.名词', '1. A noun sometimes modifies another noun. 一个名词有时候修饰另一个名词。 2. Put this noun in to the nominative. 把这个名词用于主格。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gasp', '[ɡæsp]', 'v.喘气；喘息；渴望 n.喘气', '1. He gasped out the message. 他喘着气说出了这个消息。 2. I gasped as I jumped into the cold river. 当我跳进冰冷的河里时，简直透不过气来。 3. I gasped with surprise at the unexpected news. 听到意外的消息，我惊讶地吸了一口气。 4. The exhausted runner was gasping for air. 那人跑得疲惫已极，上气不接下气。 5. Michelle recognized him and gave a gasp of shock. 米歇尔认出了他，吃惊地直喘气。', '过去式: gasped 过去分词: gasped 现在分词: gasping 第三人称单数: gasps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bacterium', '[bæk\'tɪriəm]', 'n.细菌', '1. Most of disease is caused from bacterium. 大多数疾病都是由细菌引起的。 2. A bacterium was identified as the cause for his duodenal ulcer. 一种细菌被断定为造成他十二指肠溃疡的根源。', '名词复数: bacteria');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whom', '[huːm]', 'pron.[who的宾格]谁', '1. I don\'t know whom he has in mind for the job. 我不知道他想让谁来做这项工作。 2. From whom did you learn that he was ill? 你从谁那儿知道他生病了？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('somebody', '[\'sʌmbədi]', 'pron.某人；有人 n.重要人物', '1. Somewhere somebody sometimes does something good. 在某处某人有时做某些好事。 2. Since somebody let the gardener go. 某人让园丁卷铺盖了。 3. Somebody has poked a hole in the paper screen. 有人在那个纸屏风上戳了个洞。 4. Somebody gave me a ticket for a pop concert. 有人给了我一张通俗音乐会的票。 5. I reasoned that somebody important must have been at the other end of the line. 我揣摩着这件事的背后必定有重要人物在指挥。', '名词复数: somebodies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('restaurant', '[\'restrɑːnt]', 'n.餐馆；饭店', '1. This restaurant gets three stars in the guidebook. 这家餐馆在旅游指南中标有三颗星。 2. There are many streamers in front of the restaurant. 饭店门前有许多长条旗。 3. I had my breakfast in the small restaurant. 我在一家小饭馆里吃了早饭。 4. The quality of service in this restaurant has improved a lot. 这个饭店的服务质量已经有了很大改善。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blackmail', '[\'blækmeɪl]', 'n.勒索；敲诈 vt.勒索；讹诈', '1. She was sent to prison for blackmail. 因犯敲诈勒索罪她被送进监牢。 2. It\'s a clear case of blackmail! 这显然是敲诈！ 3. He can be ruthless in getting what he wants, but I believe he would stop short of blackmail. 他这个人为达到目的是心黑手辣的,但我认为他还不至于使用敲诈手段。 4. Someone was trying to blackmail him with pictures of him and his mistress. 有人想用他和情人的照片来敲诈勒索他。', '名词: blackmailer');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inverse', '[ˌɪn\'vɜːrs]', 'adj.倒转的；相反的 n.倒数；相反的事物；(数学)逆反函数；负数', '1. Subtraction is the inverse operation of addition. 减法是加法的逆运算。 2. When you define certain operators, Visual Basic requires that you also define the operator for the inverse operation. 当定义某些特定的运算符时,Visual Basic还要求定义该运算符的逆运算。 3. The inverse of its slope is the speed of light. 其倾斜的倒数是光速。 4. The logarithmic function is defined as the inverse of the exponential function. 对数函数是作为指数函数的反函数来定义的。', '副词: inversely');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bush', '[bʊʃ]', 'n.灌木丛；矮树 v.丛生；(以灌木)标记、保护、支撑 Bush. n.布什(姓氏)', '1. He scrabbled about in the bush for the ball. 他在灌木丛中爬着到处找球。 2. The rabbit started from the bush. 野兔从灌木丛中突然窜了出来。 3. There is some ice in the bush. 树丛里有些冰。 4. With a few quick snips of the shears he pruned the bush. 他用大剪刀几下子就把灌木给修剪好了。 5. If you cut off some of the branches,the tree would not bush out. 如果你砍掉一些树枝的话，这棵树就不会枝杈丛生。 6. There are many anecdotes about George Bush. 有很多关于布什的有趣的故事。', '过去式: bushed 过去分词: bushed 现在分词: bushing 第三人称单数: bushes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brace', '[breɪs]', 'v.防备；支撑；绷紧；振作 n.支柱；支架；牙箍；一对；（复）吊带裤；大括号', '1. It is urgent that we brace against hurricanes. 我们必须做好防飓风的准备。 2. The struts are firmly braced. 那些支柱上得很牢固。 3. She braced herself against the wall. 她靠在墙上。 4. He faced the angry crowd, his arms folded, his legs braced. 面对着愤怒的人群,他抱紧双臂,绷紧双腿。 5. The odor of souls is a brace to the walls. 灵魂的气息是这些砖墙的支柱。', '过去式: braced 过去分词: braced 现在分词: bracing 第三人称单数: braces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lever', '[\'levər]', 'n.杠杆；控制杆；手段 v.撬开；使用杠杆', '1. He employed his knife as a lever. 他把刀子当杠杆用。 2. This lever must serve some ulterior purpose. 这撬棒准是用于不可告人的目的的。 3. Push hard and the lever will go down. 用力推就能把控制杆按下去。 4. Move this lever to change gear. 换档时扳动这根操纵杆。 5. They managed to lever the door open. 他们设法撬开了门。', '过去式: levered 过去分词: levered 现在分词: levering 第三人称单数: levers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ring', '[rɪŋ]', 'n.戒指；环；圈；拳击场；马戏场；帮派 n.铃声；钟声；电话；口气 v.包围；环绕；形成圈 v.打电话；回响；鸣响；按铃；听上去', '1. She wears a wedding ring to show that she\'s married. 她戴着结婚戒指，表示她已结婚。 2. Roger made the rope fast to the metal ring. 罗杰把绳子牢牢地拴在金属环上。 3. Adenine has a purine ring structure. 腺嘌呤具有嘌呤环的结构。 4. The children sat in a ring round the teacher. 孩子们围着老师坐成一圈。 5. There was a ring at the door. 门铃响了。 6. Ring the correct answer with your pencil. 用铅笔圈出正确的答案。 7. Ask her to ring me up if you should see her. 你万一见到她,请让她给我打电话。', '过去式: rang/ringed 过去分词: rung/ringed 现在分词: ringing 第三人称单数: rings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('limb', '[lɪm]', 'n.肢体；枝干；树枝 vt.肢解', '1. Men and women have four limbs; two arms and two legs. 人都有四肢，两只胳膊两条腿。 2. He stood up and stretched his limbs. 他站起来,伸了伸胳膊和腿。 3. A grey squirrel is scampering from limb to limb. 一只灰色的松鼠在树枝间跳来跳去。 4. The workers saw off a limb from the tree. 工人从树上锯下了一根大树枝。', '过去式: limbed 过去分词: limbed 现在分词: limbing 第三人称单数: limbs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('build', '[bɪld]', 'v.建造；开发；创建；逐渐增强 n.体格；身材', '1. That house is built of bricks. 那座房子是砖造的。 2. They planed to build a new laboratory. 他们计划建造一个新的实验室。 3. It is not an easy task to build a business. 创业并不是一件容易的事情。 4. We should study hard to build a better future for ourselves. 我们应该努力学习,为自己创造更美好的未来。 5. She really did not have the build for a ballerina. 她实际上并没有一个芭蕾舞女演员的体格。', '过去式: built 过去分词: built 现在分词: building 第三人称单数: builds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('buy', '[baɪ]', 'vt.购买；买；获得；收买；<俚>相信 vi.买 n.购买；便宜货', '1. Money can\'t buy happiness. 金钱买不来幸福。 2. I bought him a drink in return for his help. 我请他喝酒以酬谢他的帮助。 3. I\'d like to buy a strong household bleach. 我想买强力家用漂白剂。 4. Don\'t buy a used car from that rogue. 别从那无赖手里买旧车。 5. A lot of people just come into the shop without buying. 有很多人进店但却不购物。 6. It\'s a good buy at that price. 这是一笔价钱合算的买卖。', '形容词: buyable 过去式: bought 过去分词: bought 现在分词: buying 第三人称单数: buys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('capacity', '[kə\'pæsəti]', 'n.容量；容积；能力；职位；资格', '1. That bowl has a capacity of two pints. 那只碗的容量有两品脱。 2. What is the capacity of this jug? 这个水壶的容积多大? 3. He has a great capacity for learning languages. 他学语言的能力很强。 4. China\'s grain production capacity has improved. 中国的粮食生产能力提高了。', '名词复数: capacities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dilemma', '[dɪ\'lemə]', 'n.困境；进退两难', '1. In the process of modern urban development, we often find ourselves in a dilemma. 在都市的发展中,我们往往会陷入困境。 2. The bad weather put us in a dilemma——shall we move on or go back? 糟糕的天气使我们进退两难——是继续前进呢,还是打道回府？', '形容词: dilemmatic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('funny', '[\'fʌni]', 'adj.可笑的；有趣的；滑稽的；奇怪的；非法的', '1. The story was very funny. 这个故事非常可笑。 2. He closed his speech with a funny joke. 他用一则有趣的笑话结束了演讲。 3. Her hair was done up in a very funny way. 她的头发非常滑稽地盘在头上。 4. My funny drawings amused the children. 我的滑稽的图画把孩子们给逗乐了。', '副词: funnily 比较级: funnier 最高级: funniest 名词: funniness 名词复数: funnies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cigaret', '[ˌsɪgə\'ret]', 'n.香烟 =cigarette.', '1. I could hardly see her through the haze of cigaret smoke. 在香烟的烟雾弥漫中，我简直看不见她。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heroic', '[hə\'roʊɪk]', 'adj.英雄的；英勇的；巨大的', '1. No amount of imperialists\'bombs could blot out this heroic city. 不管帝国主义者投多少炸弹也不能把这座英雄的城市消灭掉。 2. Goya finds ways to deny the human figure that heroic role. 哥雅找到否认人的这样的英雄的脚色的办法。 3. Saving the child\'s life was a heroic act. 抢救那孩子的生命是英勇的行为。 4. Many heroic men and women have died in defense of liberty. 许多英勇的男男女女为捍卫自由而牺牲。', '副词: heroically 名词: heroicalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gallon', '[\'ɡælən]', 'n.加仑(容量单位)', '1. There are eight pints in a gallon. 一加仑有八品脱。 2. This type of car can run 25 miles a gallon. 这种汽车每加仑油料能行驶二十五英里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wealth', '[welθ]', 'n.【U】财富；财产；丰富；大量', '1. Health is better than wealth. 【谚】健康胜于财富。 2. He\'s always flaunting his wealth. 他总是摆阔。 3. She is responsible for the character part of the hero\'s devoted mother. 她负责这个主人公的忠诚的母亲的角色部分。 4. He has gambled away all his wealth. 他赌博输掉了全部财产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nucleus', '[\'nuːkliəs]', 'n.核；核心；细胞核；原子核', '1. A nucleus can have only one Y-chromosome. 一个核可以仅有一个Y染色体。 2. These council will form the nucleus of a future regime. 这些委员会将成为一个未来政权的核心。 3. These paintings will form the nucleus of a new collection. 这些油画将是新收藏品的核心。 4. These 1000 books will form the nucleus of the new school library. 这一千本书将构成学校新图书馆藏书的基础。', '名词复数: nuclei');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aggressive', '[ə\'ɡresɪv]', 'adj.侵略的；进攻性的；好斗的；有进取心的', '1. He has an aggressive manner. 他的态度咄咄逼人。 2. His style of argument in meetings is not so much aggressive as pertinacious. 他在会议上的辩论态度并非锋芒逼人而是坚持己见。 3. Red fire ants are very aggressive and readily attack anything that disturb them. 红火蚁攻击性强,容易攻击任何干扰它们的生物。 4. America has a lot of aggressive weapons now. 美国现在有很多进攻性武器。', '副词: aggressively 名词: aggressiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('output', '[\'aʊtpʊt]', 'n.产量；输出功率；输出 vt.输出(信息等)', '1. Output has tripled. 产量已增加到三倍。 2. This country ranks last in industrial output. 这个国家的工业生产排名最後。 3. The average output of the factory is 20 cars a day. 该工厂的平均产量是每天20辆汽车。 4. Have you got the one which has an output of 150 horsepower? 你们有没有输出功率是一百五十（150）马力的? 5. The printer will output colour chart. 打印机将会输出彩色图表。', '过去式: outputted/output 过去分词: outputted/output 现在分词: outputting 第三人称单数: outputs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remember', '[rɪ\'membər]', 'v.记得；想起；记住，铭记；回忆；提及', '1. I remember his objecting to the scheme. 我记得他曾经反对该计划。 2. Remember to write us when you get there. 到了那儿别忘了给我们写信。 3. I\'m sorry, I can\'t remember your name. 对不起，我想不起你的名字了。 4. I really can\'t remember what you said last night. 我确实记不得你昨天晚上说了什么。', '形容词: rememberable 名词: rememberability 过去式: remembered 过去分词: remembered 现在分词: remembering 第三人称单数: remembers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('income', '[\'ɪnkʌm]', 'n.收入；所得；收益', '1. His income is well below the average. 他的收入大大低于平均水平。 2. My monthly income was just over 200 pounds. 我每月的收入是200多磅。 3. He needs a high income to support such a large family. 他需要有高收入才能供养得起这样一个大家庭。 4. The money I got was a useful supplement to my ordinary income. 我得到的那笔钱是很管用的外快。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('background', '[\'bækɡraʊnd]', 'n.背景；经历；幕后；后景 vt.提供背景', '1. He has a strong political background. 他有强大的政治背景。 2. It is wrong to differentiate between people according to their family background. 根据出身不同而区别待人是不对的。 3. With my working-class background I feel like a fish out of water among these high-society people. 我出身于工人阶级,在上流社会中感到很不自在。 4. Her marketing background made her a natural choice for the job. 她的经销经历使她成为这一职位的必然人选。 5. To background themselves, reporters dug through all available files on the case. 为掌握有关背景资料,记者们搜集了对此案有关的可获得的所有文件资料。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('composite', '[kəm\'pɑːzət]', 'adj.合成的；复合的 n.合成物；复合材料', '1. The police artist made a composite picture of the murderer. 警察局的拼图师拼出了一幅谋杀罪犯的图片。 2. The play is a composite of reality and fiction. 该剧是现实与想象的合成。 3. English is a composite of many languages. 英语是多种语言混合而成的。 4. The main character in her latest novel is a composite of several public figures of that era. 她最近发布的小说中的主人公是那个时代几个公众人物的结合体。', '副词: compositely 名词: compositeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('economical', '[ˌiːkə\'nɑːmɪkl]', 'adj.节俭的；经济的；合算的', '1. She is an economical housekeeper and feeds her family cheaply. 她是一个节俭的家庭主妇，她全家的花销不大。 2. We are advocate economical life. 我们提倡俭朴的生活。 3. This is not an economical method of heating. 这不是一种经济的取暖方式。 4. She writes novels with economical style. 她以简练的风格写小说。', '副词: economically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('across', '[ə\'krɔːs]', 'adv.横过；穿过；朝向特定的方向；在对面；横写地 prep.横过；穿过；在对面；在(身体某部位)上；在…各处', '1. Can you swim across the river? 你能游到河的对岸吗？ 2. The drunk man staggered across the room. 那个醉汉摇摇晃晃地穿过房间。 3. Edgar looked in anger across at Miriam. 埃德加气鼓鼓地看着对面的米丽安。 4. When my name was called, he looked across at me. 当叫到我名字的时候，他从那边朝我看过来。 5. A big tree fell across the ditch. 一棵大树横贯沟渠倒下。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('petty', '[\'peti]', 'adj.小的；琐碎的；次要的；狭隘的', '1. The party split into petty factions. 该党分裂成若干小派系。 2. The paymasters of these petty crooks are the big crime syndicates. 操纵这帮小流氓的就是那个大犯罪集团。 3. In his short life he had run the entire gamut of crime, from petty theft to murder. 他在短短的一生中,从小偷小摸到杀人,什么罪都犯过。 4. Don\'t bug me with petty details. 不要讲那些琐碎的细节来烦我。', '副词: pettily 比较级: pettier 最高级: pettiest 名词: pettiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tragedy', '[\'trædʒədi]', 'n.悲剧；灾难；惨事', '1. Tragedy is in store for that poor girl from the beginning. 从一开始，那个女孩的悲剧就是不可避免的。 2. Shakespeare\'s Hamlet is a very famous tragedy. 莎士比亚的《哈姆雷特》是一部十分著名的悲剧。 3. It was not long before tragedy struck again. 没多久，灾难又再次降临。 4. This recent tragedy has put the manufacturersof the drug squarely in the dock. 新近发生的这一悲惨事件使药品厂商受到指控。', '名词复数: tragedies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('messenger', '[\'mesɪndʒər]', 'n.报信者；先兆', '1. Maybe I can act as a messenger for you. 也许我能给你当信差。 2. Some have feared it as a messenger of evil. 有些人害怕它是个不吉利的兆头。', '过去式: messengered 过去分词: messengered 现在分词: messengering 第三人称单数: messengers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('profile', '[\'proʊfaɪl]', 'n.侧面；轮廓；形象；简介 v.描绘 ... 轮廓；评论人物', '1. I photographed him in profile. 我从侧面给他拍照。 2. She is prettier in profile than at full face. 她的侧面比正面好看。 3. We could see the profile of a distant hill if it is very clear. 如果天气晴朗, 我们可看到远山的轮廓。 4. The deal will certainly raise the company\'s international profile. 这宗交易肯定会提高这家公司的国际形象。 5. The huge trees were profiled against the night sky. 在夜空的映衬下显出大树的轮廓。', '名词: profiler 过去式: profiled 过去分词: profiled 现在分词: profiling 第三人称单数: profiles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('articulate', '[ɑːr\'tɪkjuleɪt]', 'adj.发音清晰的；善于表达的；有关节的 v.清楚地讲话；发音；以关节连接', '1. Articulate speech is essential for a teacher. 对教师来说,口齿清楚是必不可少的。 2. I\'m a little deaf, please articulate your words carefully. 我有些耳聋，请把话仔细地说清楚。 3. She\'s unusually articulate for a ten-year-old. 作为一个十岁的孩子来说，她的表达力是非常强的。 4. Young people are articulate about the skills they need for everyday life. 年轻人善于表达他们应付日常生活所需的技能。 5. She was too frightened to articulate. 她吓得连话也说不清。', '副词: articulately 名词: articulateness 过去式: articulated 过去分词: articulated 现在分词: articulating 第三人称单数: articulates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('revenue', '[\'revənuː]', 'n.税收；收入；税务局', '1. National tax revenue grew by a large margin every year. 国家税收连年大幅度增长。 2. The state does not collect enough revenue to cover its expenditure. 政府征收的税收不能满足支出。 3. Rent is one form of revenue. 房租是一种收入。 4. The document states that all revenue has to be declared to the tax office. 该文件规定必须向税务局申报所有收入。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('procedure', '[prə\'siːdʒər]', 'n.程序；手续；步骤', '1. These procedures are highly irregular. 这些程序是很不合乎规则的。 2. What\'s the procedure for opening a savings account? 开一个储蓄帐户有什么手续? 3. The next procedure is to insert the battery. 接下来的步骤是装进电池。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('just', '[dʒʌst]', 'adv.刚才；仅仅；正好；正是；简直 adj.公平的；公正的；适当的；精确的', '1. This is the thing you just left. 这是您刚才忘在这里的东西。 2. I am just teasing you; you need not be nervous. 我仅仅是在跟你闹着玩,你不要紧张。 3. I\'m sorry, but I am just on my way out. 很抱歉,我正好要出门。 4. To our great joy, your goods arrived just in time. 令我们欣喜若狂的是,你的物资来的正是时候。 5. Our aim is a just and lasting peace. 我们的目标是维持一个公平而持久和平的世界。', '副词: justly 名词: justness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('organization', '[ˌɔːrɡənə\'zeɪʃn]', 'n.机构；组织 adj.有组织的', '1. Our company is the epitome of a well organized, efficient organization. 我们公司是一个组织完备、有效率的典範机构。 2. They have established a student organization. 他们建立了一个学生组织。 3. He\'s involved in the organization of a new club. 他参与了新俱乐部的组织工作。 4. Organization of the company was then in a state of flux. 当时公司的编制正处于不稳定状态。', '形容词: organizational 副词: organizationally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compromise', '[\'kɑːmprəmaɪz]', 'n.妥协；折衷；折衷案；和解 vt.妥协处理；危害 vi.妥协，和解；让步', '1. He did it without compromise of his dignity. 他做这事而不损及他的尊严。 2. The agreement is a compromise, not a sell-out. 这个协议是双方妥协的产物而不是一方让步。 3. After some discussion we arrive at a compromise. 经过一番讨论之后，我们达成一项折衷方案。 4. Or are we ready to compromise our faith? 或者，我们准备好了在信仰上折衷吗？ 5. With this increased awareness, attackers are finding it more difficult to compromise systems at the network level. 由于对这些认识得越来越清楚，攻击者发现在网络级上危害系统更加困难。 6. They found it wiser to compromise with her. 他们觉得与她妥协更明智。', '名词: compromiser 过去式: compromised 过去分词: compromised 现在分词: compromising 第三人称单数: compromises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('doze', '[doʊz]', 'v.打瞌睡 n.瞌睡', '1. He dozed off during the class. 他上课打瞌睡。 2. He closed his eyes and seemed to doze. 他闭上眼睛，好像在打瞌睡。 3. We couldn\'t help but doze off during his lecture. 他演讲时我们不得不打瞌睡。 4. He fell into a doze. 他打起盹儿来了。', '名词: dozer 过去式: dozed 过去分词: dozed 现在分词: dozing 第三人称单数: dozes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dictionary', '[\'dɪkʃəneri]', 'n.字典；辞典；词典', '1. That is not, properly speaking, a dictionary but a grammar book. 严格地说，那不是一本字典，而是一本语法书。 2. He is, as it were, a walking dictionary. 他可说是个活字典。 3. That dictionary belongs to me. 那本字典是属于我的。 4. A dictionary is an invaluable aid in learning a new language. 在学习一种新语言时,辞典是非常有用的工具。', '名词复数: dictionaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bizarre', '[bɪ\'zɑːr]', 'adj.奇异的；怪诞的', '1. The building was of bizarre construction. 这建筑构造奇异。 2. She got herself up in a bizarre outfit. 她穿了一套古怪的套装 3. Its bizarre quality was not lost on us. 我们没有被那种异乎寻常的气氛弄得晕头转向。 4. His bizarre behavior attracted our attention. 他怪诞的行为吸引了我们的注意力。', '副词: bizarrely 名词: bizarreness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('static', '[\'stætɪk]', 'adj.静态的；静止的；稳定的；静力的；静电的 n.静电；静电干扰', '1. The winking eye is implemented as a series of static images. 眨动的眼睛是用一系列静态图像实现的。 2. Such principles as self-government, or freedom, or social welfare, are not static but dynamic. 自治,自由,或社会福利等原则并非静止,而是变动的。 3. House prices, which have been static for several months, are now rising again. 房价稳定了几个月，现在又上涨了。 4. Static friction is greater than sliding fricton. 静摩擦力大于滑动摩擦力。 5. Her hair was full of static. 她的头发上静电很强。', '形容词: statical 副词: statically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('advent', '[\'ædvent]', 'n.出现；到来', '1. The advent of the computer changed people\'s life greatly. 计算机的出现极大地改变了人们的生活。 2. With the advent of the rockets, the Space Age began. 随着火箭的出现,太空时代开始了。 3. The advent of the Euro will redefine Europe. 欧元的出现将重新定义欧洲。 4. With the advent of spring, everything comes to life again. 随着春天的到来，万物复苏了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rub', '[rʌb]', 'v.擦；摩擦；搓；惹恼 n.困难；障碍；擦', '1. I rubbed the window with a cloth. 我用一块布擦窗子。 2. We may have to rub polish on the floor. 我们可能得在地板上涂上光剂了。 3. He asked me to rub up the silver. 他让我把银器擦一擦。 4. The wheel\'s rubbing on the mudguard. 车轮蹭著了挡泥板。 5. We need money badly, but there\'s the rub: no one will lend us any. 我们急需要钱,但困难的是:谁也不会借钱给我们。', '过去式: rubbed 过去分词: rubbed 现在分词: rubbing 第三人称单数: rubs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('analogue', '[\'ænəlɔːɡ]', 'n.类似物 adj.模拟的，模拟计算机的', '1. The gill of a fish is the analogue of the lung of a cat. 鱼的鳃和猫的肺是类似物。 2. A vegetarian gets protein not from meat but from its analogues. 素食者所摄取的蛋白质不是来自肉类而是来自近似肉类的食物。 3. In a sense, the act of counterfeiting can be seen as an analogue to my own artistic practice. 从某种意义上说，这种伪造行为是我自身艺术实践的一种翻版。 4. Generally, voice transmission is in analogue form. 通常，声音的传送是用模拟形式。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prepare', '[prɪ\'per]', 'v.预备；准备', '1. Early experiments with military rockets prepared the ground for space travel. 早年对军用火箭进行的实验为发展航天技术奠定了基础。 2. He is preparing his speech for the meeting tomorrow. 他正准备明天集会的演说。 3. Prepare to alight,for we are almost there. 我们马上就要到了 4. Peel the pineapples and I will prepare the pineapple pie. 你把菠萝皮削了,我来准备菠萝派。', '副词: preparedly 名词: preparer 过去式: prepared 过去分词: prepared 现在分词: preparing 第三人称单数: prepares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('disgust', '[dɪs\'ɡʌst]', 'n.厌恶；憎恶；反感 vt.使厌恶；使作呕', '1. She turned away in disgust. 她厌恶地转过脸去。 2. His behavior filled her with disgust. 她对他的行为充满了厌恶。 3. He returned downstairs in disgust. 他厌恶地转身下楼。 4. I can only feel disgust for these criminals. 对这些罪犯我只感到憎恶。 5. His ideas disgust me; they are terrible. 他的一些想法使我很反感，它们实在是太可怕了。', '过去式: disgusted 过去分词: disgusted 现在分词: disgusting 第三人称单数: disgusts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enjoy', '[ɪn\'dʒɔɪ]', 'v.享受；喜欢', '1. Now that I am free, I can enjoy music for a while. 既然有空，我可以享受一下音乐。 2. They enjoy the fruits of their hard labor. 他们享受自己辛勤努力的成果。 3. How did you enjoy the concert? 你喜欢那场音乐会吗？ 4. I enjoy reading Mark Twain\'s autobiography. 我喜欢读马克•吐温的自传。', '形容词: enjoyable 副词: enjoyably 名词: enjoyment 过去式: enjoyed 过去分词: enjoyed 现在分词: enjoying 第三人称单数: enjoys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('promising', '[\'prɑːmɪsɪŋ]', 'adj.有希望的；有前途的', '1. After a promising start, the project soon fizzled out. 这项计划开始时很有希望,但不久就失败了。 2. For a time he was looked on as a promising writer. 人们一度认为他是一个有希望的作家。 3. The results of the experiments are very promising. 实验的结果充满了希望。 4. The coach is bringing on some promising youngsters in the reserve team. 教练正在帮助后备队中有前途的年轻人提高技术。', '副词: promisingly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('do', '[du]', 'v.做；干 n.注意事项；<非正式>聚会；<古>事情', '1. He is doing his homework. 他正在做他的家庭作业。 2. Do what I tell you. 按照我告诉你的去做。 3. To tell you the truth, I hate to do it. 老实告诉你,我不愿意做这事。 4. He did little work that day. 那天他没有干什么工作。', '名词复数: do\'s 过去式: did 过去分词: done 现在分词: doing 第三人称单数: does');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spill', '[spɪl]', 'v.溢出；洒；使 ... 流出；泄漏 n.溢出；流；木片；小杆', '1. The coffee is so full that it might spill over. 咖啡太满可能会溢出来。 2. Put the cap back on the bottle, otherwise the juice will spill. 把瓶盖儿盖好，要不汁液就洒出来了。 3. Take care not to spill a drop of the medicine. 注意一滴药也不要洒。 4. The sway of the pail cause some milk to spill out. 桶的摇晃使一些牛奶溢了出来。 5. The oil spill endangered thousands of birds. 石油的溢泄危及成千上万的鸟儿。', '名词: spiller 过去式: spilled/spilt 过去分词: spilled/spilt 现在分词: spilling 第三人称单数: spills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('queen', '[kwiːn]', 'n.王后；女王', '1. The queen consort has come together with the king. 王后也随同国王前来。 2. Mary, Queen of Scots, was put to death in1587. 苏格兰王后玛丽于1587年被处死。 3. They were bowing as the king and queen walking in. 当国王和王后进来时他们屈膝致敬。 4. The Pope was present at the coronation of Queen Elizabeth II. 教皇参加了伊丽莎白二世的加冕礼。', '过去式: queened 过去分词: queened 现在分词: queening 第三人称单数: queens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rain', '[reɪn]', 'n.雨；雨水 v.下雨；(雨点般)落下', '1. There will be rain in all parts of the country. 全国各地将有雨。 2. The boys went for a walk despite of the rain. 尽管下雨，孩子们还是去散步。 3. The rain beat against the windows. 雨水拍打在窗户上。 4. Too much rain accounted for the poor crop. 太多的雨水导致庄稼歉收。 5. If it doesn\'t rain tomorrow, we\'ll have a picnic. 如果明天不下雨，我们就去野餐。', '形容词: rainless 过去式: rained 过去分词: rained 现在分词: raining 第三人称单数: rains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('connect', '[kə\'nekt]', 'v.连接；接通；联系', '1. The plumber connected up all the pipes and turned on the tap. 管子工连接上所有管子，然后打开了水龙头。 2. These terminals are connected to our mainframe computer. 这些终端设备都和我们的计算机主机相连。 3. Has the phone been connected yet? 电话接通了吗？ 4. The police tried to connect him with the murder. 警方试图将他与这起谋杀案联系起来。', '形容词: connectible 名词: connector 过去式: connected 过去分词: connected 现在分词: connecting 第三人称单数: connects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recover', '[rɪ\'kʌvər]', 'v.恢复；复原；重获', '1. He\'s now fully recovered from his stroke. 他现已从中风病完全康复了。 2. He is very ill and unlikely to recover. 他病得非常厉害，不大可能恢复健康了。 3. I nearly fell but managed to recover myself. 我差一点倒下,但最后还是站稳了脚根。 4. I sat down to recover from my agitation. 我坐下以使自己平静下来。', '形容词: recoverable 名词: recoverer 过去式: recovered 过去分词: recovered 现在分词: recovering 第三人称单数: recovers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hair', '[her]', 'n.头发；毛发；极少量', '1. I\'ll have my hair trimmed tomorrow. 明天我要修剪头发。 2. She wears her hair in a bun. 她把头发盘成一个髻。 3. Hair is easy to collect and convenient to store. 毛发既容搜集又便于保存。 4. She won by a hair. 她以微弱的优势获胜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('competent', '[\'kɑːmpɪtənt]', 'adj.有能力的；足够的；胜任的', '1. Her drawing is competent, but her composition is poor. 她的画有功力，但布局欠佳。 2. She was declared mentally competent to stand trial. 她被宣告有接受审判的精神能力。 3. He is competent enough to fill that position. 他完全胜任那个职位。 4. Is Mary competent as a teacher? 玛丽胜任教师的工作吗？', '副词: competently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deed', '[diːd]', 'n.行为；事迹；[法]契约 vt.立契转让', '1. His deed claims our respect. 他的行为值得我们尊敬。 2. His deed revealed him to be a kind man. 他的行为显示他是个好心的人。 3. We must take the consequences of our own deed. 我们必须承担自己行为的后果。 4. We had a heated discussion in honour of their heroic deed. 为了纪念他们的英雄事迹,我们举行了一次热烈的讨论会。 5. The widow decided to deed the house over to her nephew before she died. 那寡妇决定在去世前把房子立契转让给她侄子。', '过去式: deeded 过去分词: deeded 现在分词: deeding 第三人称单数: deeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assume', '[ə\'suːm]', 'vt.假定；设想；承担；(想当然的)认为；假装', '1. Let\'s assume it to be true. 让我们假定这是真的。 2. We assume his guilt. 我们假定他是有罪的。 3. They assumed their operational positions. 他们设想了自己在实施中的作用。 4. I am not afraid to assume the responsibility. 我不怕承担责任.', '形容词: assumable 副词: assumably 名词: assumer 过去式: assumed 过去分词: assumed 现在分词: assuming 第三人称单数: assumes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('presently', '[\'prezntli]', 'adv.不久；一会儿；现在；目前', '1. Presently I got the whole story. 不久我便了解了整个事件。 2. Presently we heard a bustle, and a tread of feet. 不久我们听到一阵喧噪声，和脚步声。 3. The doctor will be here presently. 医生一会儿就到。 4. Presently she excused herself and went home. 一会儿，她就托故告辞回家了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yield', '[jiːld]', 'v.生产；获利；屈服；弯下去 n.投资收益；生产量', '1. The village abounds in fields that yield many bushels of corn. 那个村庄到处都是盛产玉米的农田。 2. The combined investment is expected to yield $5,000 in the first year. 第一年该总投资有望获利5000美元。 3. We\' ve already made it clear that we will not yield to pressure. 我们已经表明我们不会屈服于压力。 4. The shelf is beginning to yield under that heavy weight. 架子被那么大的重量压得弯了下去。 5. So if the share price rises and the dividend does not, then the yield falls. 因此，如果股份上涨而股息不变，收益就下跌。', '名词: yielder 过去式: yielded 过去分词: yielded 现在分词: yielding 第三人称单数: yields');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('impetus', '[\'ɪmpɪtəs]', 'n.推动力；刺激', '1. His articles provided the main impetus for change. 他的那些文章是促进变革的主要推动力。 2. The present conflict may provide fresh impetus for peace talk. 目前的冲突可能会给和谈提供新的推动力。 3. Her speech gave an impetus to my ideas. 她的讲话激发了我的思绪。 4. His articles provided the main impetus for change. 他的那些文章是促进变革的主要推动力。', '名词复数: impetuses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('giggle', '[\'ɡɪɡl]', 'v.咯咯地笑 n.咯咯笑；趣事', '1. Stop giggling, children; this is a serious matter. 孩子们，别傻笑了，这是严肃的事情。 2. The children couldn\'t stop giggling at the teacher\'s high-pitched voice. 教师的嗓音很高，孩子们都不禁咯咯地笑起来。 3. There was a giggle from the back of the class. 从教室后面传来咯咯的笑声。 4. What a giggle! 多有意思的玩意儿！', '形容词: giggly 副词: gigglingly 名词: giggler 过去式: giggled 过去分词: giggled 现在分词: giggling 第三人称单数: giggles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('destination', '[ˌdestɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.目的地；终点', '1. We eventually arrived at our destination. 我们终于到达了目的地。 2. The parcel was sent to the wrong destination. 包裹送错了地方。 3. The coach followed a rather devious course to its destination. 长途汽车要绕很多弯路才到达目的地。 4. The destination of bus No. 8 is the State University. 8路车的终点是州立大学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('awake', '[ə\'weɪk]', 'adj.醒着的；警觉的 v.唤起；唤醒；醒来', '1. The children are still wide awake. 孩子们仍然完全醒着。 2. The smart of his wound kept him awake. 伤痛使他无法入睡。 3. A pilot must be awake to the changes in the weather. 飞行员必须警觉天气的变化。 4. He is awake to the serious problem. 他已意识到这个严重的问题。 5. Nothing can awake her interest in this trip. 没有东西可唤起她对这次旅行的兴趣。', '过去式: awoke/awaked 过去分词: awaked/awoken 现在分词: awaking 第三人称单数: awakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('smash', '[smæʃ]', 'v.打碎；粉碎；猛撞 n.破碎；撞击；轰动的演出；[网球]高压扣球 adj.极为成功的', '1. The bottle slipped and smashed to pieces on the floor. 瓶子滑在地上,摔成碎片。 2. We shall thoroughly smash the scheme of the enemy. 我们要彻底粉碎敌人的阴谋。 3. We must be ready at all times to smash the enemy\'s attacks. 我们必须随时准备粉碎敌人的进攻。 4. I lost my key and had to smash the window open. 我把钥匙弄丢了,只好把窗户撞开进屋了。 5. The teapot fell with an awful smash. 茶壶掉下来摔得粉碎。 6. The play had its smash premiere. 那出戏首场演出引起了极大的轰动。', '名词: smasher 过去式: smashed 过去分词: smashed 现在分词: smashing 第三人称单数: smashes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fossil', '[\'fɑːsl]', 'n.化石；食古不化的人；守旧的事物', '1. Coal is a fossil fuel. 煤是一种矿物燃料。 2. This fossil may be over 2 million years old. 这化石可能超过二百万年了。 3. He found a piece of fossil of an ancient bird. 他发现一块古代鸟类的化石。 4. Professor Baboon is not an old fossil. 巴布恩教授不是落伍的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('frustrate', '[\'frʌstreɪt]', 'vt.挫败；击败；使沮丧；使灰心 adj.无益的；挫败的；挫折的', '1. This is the place that we frustrate enemy. 这是我们挫败敌人的地方。 2. They made their preparations to frustrate the conspiracy. 他们作好准备挫败以这个阴谋。 3. The terrible weather frustrated our hopes of going out. 恶劣的天气使我们外出的愿望无法实现。 4. We have the confidence in frustrating our enemy. 我们有信心击败敌人。 5. The prisoner made a frustrate attempt to escape. 囚犯妄图逃跑。', '副词: frustratingly 名词: frustrater 过去式: frustrated 过去分词: frustrated 现在分词: frustrating 第三人称单数: frustrates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('surgery', '[\'sɜːrdʒəri]', 'n.外科手术；外科；诊所；手术室', '1. He is preparing for the surgery. 他正在做手术前的准备。 2. He underwent open-heart surgery. 他接受了体外循环心脏手术。 3. He is a plastic surgery specialist. 他是个整形外科医生。 4. I want you to go to the hospital surgery for a general check-up. 希望你到外科医生的诊所进行全面检查。', '名词复数: surgeries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grasp', '[ɡræsp]', 'n.把握；领会；抓紧 vt.领会；抓住；紧握', '1. She has a good grasp of the English language. 她精通英语。 2. She has a comprehensive grasp of the subject. 她已全面掌握了这一学科。 3. I kept her hands in my grasp. 我紧握着她的手。 4. I grasped the main point of the speech. 我领会了这篇演讲的要点。', '过去式: grasped 过去分词: grasped 现在分词: grasping 第三人称单数: grasps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lamp', '[læmp]', 'n.灯；台灯；油灯；光源', '1. The lamp hung over the table. 那盏灯悬挂在桌子上方。 2. The lamp was set on my desk for me to study at night. 台灯放在我的书桌上,好让我晚上可以学习。 3. In our village, electric light has taken the place of oil lamp. 在我们村庄,电灯已经取代了油灯。 4. The flower was clearly outlined in the light of the lamp. 花朵在阳光下清晰地显现出轮廓。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('university', '[ˌjuːnɪ\'vɜːrsəti]', 'n.大学', '1. John is one of his alumni in the university. 约翰是他大学时的校友之一。 2. My uncle is a professor in this university. 我的伯父是这所大学的一名教授。 3. There are many foreign professors in this university. 这所大学有许多外国教授。 4. She majored in maths and physics at university. 她在大学期间主修数学和物理。', '名词复数: universities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fight', '[faɪt]', 'n.战斗；打架；斗志 vt.打架；对抗 vi.奋斗；斗争；争吵', '1. After spiritual purification, he meets the demon in a thrilling fight. 在精神净化后,他遇见邪魔并展开激烈的战斗。 2. Armed with raincoat and flashlight, he joined in the fight against the flood. 他穿上雨衣,带上手电,加入了抗洪的战斗。 3. Did you hear that there was a fight down in the local on Wednesday? 你听说了吗?上星期三在附近的酒馆里有人打架。 4. All the fight seemed to go out of him. 他似乎再无斗志。 5. The boxer has fought many opponents. 该拳手已与许多对手交锋。 6. She fought like a tiger to get what she wanted. 她竭力争取自己想要的东西。', '形容词: fightable 副词: fightingly 名词: fightability 过去式: fought 过去分词: fought 现在分词: fighting 第三人称单数: fights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('course', '[kɔːrs]', 'n.课程；讲座；过程；路线；一道(菜) v.跑过，穿过；追赶；快跑', '1. She took a course in philosophy. 她选读了一门哲学课程。 2. She is taking a secretarial course. 她正在上文秘课程。 3. Television has arranged an English teaching course lately. 电视台最近开设了英语讲座。 4. Events took their natural course. 事态依自然进程发展。', '过去式: coursed 过去分词: coursed 现在分词: coursing 第三人称单数: courses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('commence', '[kə\'mens]', 'v.开始；着手；<英>获得学位', '1. I commence from this point. 我从此点开始。 2. The second term commences in March. 第二学期自三月开始。 3. We will commence with this work. 我们要着手进行这项工作。 4. I commence a round of visit. 我开始着手一系列访问。', '名词: commencer 过去式: commenced 过去分词: commenced 现在分词: commencing 第三人称单数: commences');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('editorial', '[ˌedɪ\'tɔːriəl]', 'n.社论 adj.编辑的', '1. The editorial lashed out at official corruption. 那篇社论猛烈抨击官场的腐败。 2. He recomposed the editorial till dawn. 他改写社论直到天亮。 3. She has editorial control over what is included. 她有权决定编辑的内容。 4. To this moment, generally speaking, editorial anger vanished completely, absolutely won\'t reintroduce what is other requirement. 到这个时候，一般来说，编辑的愤怒就烟消云散了，绝不会再提出什么别的要求。', '副词: editorially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('boast', '[boʊst]', 'v.自夸；吹牛；以...为荣 n.自夸；引以为荣的事物', '1. Don\'t boast and don\'t be modest. 不要自夸,也不要太谦虚。 2. That\'s nothing to boast about. 那没有什麽值得自吹的。 3. Nobody should boast of his learning. 谁也不应当夸耀自己的学识。 4. He never boasted of his cleverness. 他未曾夸耀过自己的聪明。 5. That brother of yours is full of boasts. 你那个宝贝兄弟满口大话。', '形容词: boastful 副词: boastfully 名词: boaster 过去式: boasted 过去分词: boasted 现在分词: boasting 第三人称单数: boasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('some', '[səm]', 'adj.一些；若干 adv.大约；非常 pron.一些(人、物)', '1. She won a competition in some newspaper or other. 她参加某报纸举办的比赛获胜。 2. If you save some money each week, we can go on holiday. 要是你每星期能存点儿钱，咱们就可以外出度假了。 3. There is some ice in the bush. 树丛里有些冰。 4. Some mail came for you this morning. 今天上午有你的邮件。 5. Some 40 people attended the rally. 大约有40个人参加了集合 6. Some of the money was stolen. 有些钱给偷走了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('capsule', '[\'kæpsjuːl]', 'n.胶囊；太空舱；荚膜；概要 v.概括；装入胶囊 adj.精简的；微型的', '1. The capsule is filled with small soluble cases. 胶囊里充满了可溶的小颗粒。 2. This capsule is to be taken every four hours. 这种胶囊每隔四小时服一次。 3. This capsule is used for animals. 这个太空舱是用来装载动物的。 4. The capsule is a part of the spaceship in which the pilots live and work. 太空舱是宇宙飞船的一部分，宇航员是在太空舱里活动工作的。 5. Would you please capsule the news? 你能概括下这则新闻吗？ 6. This is a capsule description of the event. 这就是关于那个事件的简要介绍。', '过去式: capsuled 过去分词: capsuled 现在分词: capsuling 第三人称单数: capsules');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contribution', '[ˌkɑːntrɪ\'bjuːʃn]', 'n.贡献；捐款(赠)；投稿', '1. Don\'t undervalue Jim\'s contribution to the research. 不要低估了吉姆在研究工作中的贡献。 2. He has made an important contribution to the company\'s success. 他对公司的成功作出了重要的贡献。 3. All contribution, however small, will be greatly appreciated. 所有捐款，无论数目多么少，我们都深表感谢。 4. The union successfully negotiated increased employer contributions to the health benefits package. 工会成功地让雇主增加对医疗福利的捐赠。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cognitive', '[\'kɑːɡnətɪv]', 'adj.认识的；认知的；有认识力的', '1. Thinking in terms of dualisms is common in our cognitive culture. 我们的认识文化通常具有两重性思考。 2. The second cognitive revolution is a post-modern one and it results in the establishment of social constructionism. 第二次认知革命是后现代主义的革命,它导致了社会建构论的产生。 3. Linguistics is an important branch in cognitive science. 语言学是认知科学的一个重要分支。', '副词: cognitively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('like', '[laɪk]', 'prep.像 conj.如同 adv.大概；和 ... 一样 adj.相似的；同样的 v.喜欢；想；愿意 n.类似的人或物', '1. At a distance he looks a bit like James Bond. 从远处看，他有点像詹姆斯·邦德。 2. It\'ll rain this afternoon, as like as not. 今天下午很可能要下雨。 3. I like movies, but I don\'t like Westerns. 我喜欢电影,但不喜欢西部牛仔片。 4. I would like to have a word with you. 我想同你说句话。', '过去式: liked 过去分词: liked 现在分词: liking 第三人称单数: likes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expertise', '[ˌekspɜːr\'tiːz]', 'n.专门知识；专门技术；专家的意见', '1. He has the expertise in the management of hotels. 他有酒店管理知识。 2. I have no sewing expertise 我没有缝纫方面的知识。 3. We were amazed at his expertise on the ski slopes. 他斜坡滑雪的技能使我们赞叹不已。 4. The company is eager to develop its own expertise in the area of computer programming. 该公司希望能在计算机程序领域开发出自己的专门技术。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('random', '[\'rændəm]', 'adj.任意的；随机的；随意的 n.随意；任意 adv.随机地', '1. Men are exposed to more acts of random physical violence. 男人受到更多的任意的身体强烈活动。 2. Most people know that the outcome of a coin toss is random. 大部分人都知道掷硬币的结果是随机的。 3. The computer will generate apparently random numbers. 电脑似乎将随机产生号码。 4. This random approach is not as dubious as one might expect. 这种随意的途径并不象人们所预期的那样无把握。 5. Soiled dishes were piled at random. 脏碟子胡乱地堆放着。 6. Complex organs made up of separate but necessary subsystems cannot be the result of random chance. 复杂的器官是由独立的，必要的子系统组成，而且不能随机地形成。', '副词: randomly 名词: randomness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('extract', '[\'ekstrækt]', 'vt.摘录；提取；拔出；榨出；选取 [计算机] 提取. n.摘录；精华；榨出物', '1. She extracted passages for the students to translate. 她选了些短文让学生翻译. 2. She extracted a small notebook from her handbag. 她从手提包里取出了一个小笔记本。 3. He tried to extract his pole from the mud. 他试图用力将杆子从泥中拔出来。 4. It takes a major operation to extract money from a minor poet. 要从小诗人那儿榨出钱来，得施行一次大手术。 5. I would like to quote two extracts from the book. 我很想引用这本书的两段文字。', '形容词: extractable 名词: extractor 过去式: extracted 过去分词: extracted 现在分词: extracting 第三人称单数: extracts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('vote', '[voʊt]', 'n.选举权；投票；选举；投票结果 v.表决；选举；投票', '1. Give women the vote! 给妇女选举权！ 2. I suggested putting the matter to a vote, but the chairman demurred to it. 我建议对此事投票表决，但主席表示反对。 3. A large vote was polled. 投票踊跃。 4. He used his casting vote to block the motion. 他用他的投票反对动议的通过。 5. We are going to vote on the plan . 我们打算就这一提案进行表决。', '形容词: votable 名词: voter 过去式: voted 过去分词: voted 现在分词: voting 第三人称单数: votes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('keep', '[kiːp]', 'v.保持；保留；继续；贮藏；经营；遵守；供给；照管；饲养；耽搁；保持食物不变质；健康状况如何；保守（秘密@）；记录；遵守；保护 n.生计；保存；城堡主楼；监狱；围墙', '1. He would keep in touch with us wherever he was. 他无论在什么地方,总是与我们保持联系。 2. Here\'s a five-pound note-- you can keep the change. 这是五镑的钞票－－零钱不用找了。 3. Progress is slow but we keep battling on. 进展虽慢 4. Where do you keep the detergent? 你把清洁剂放在哪儿了？ 5. Paul earns his keep by helping his elderly landlord. 保罗靠帮助他年迈的房东干活来维持生计。', '过去式: kept 过去分词: kept 现在分词: keeping 第三人称单数: keeps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shed', '[ʃed]', 'vt.除掉；使脱落；使流出；使清晰 n.小屋；车棚', '1. This method can help students shed inhibitions. 这一方法能帮助学生去除顾虑。 2. Most trees shed their leaves in autumn. 大多数树在秋天落叶。 3. It\'s too late to change your mind now and there is no point in shedding tears. 你现在改变主意已经太迟了,而且为此伤心落泪是毫无用处的。 4. Can you shed any light on the situation? 你能说明一下这个情形吗？ 5. The snow has banked up against the shed. 雪在小屋旁聚积起来。', '过去式: shed 过去分词: shed 现在分词: shedding 第三人称单数: sheds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('efficiency', '[ɪ\'fɪʃnsi]', 'n.效率；功率', '1. We must improve our efficiency as soon as possible. 我们必须尽快地提高工作效率。 2. Their labor efficiency is very high. 他们的工作效率很高。 3. The two companies consolidated for greater efficiency. 这两家公司已合并以提高效率。 4. This jet has a very high propulsive efficiency. 该喷气机的喷射功率非常大。', '名词复数: efficiencies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('basketball', '[\'bæskɪtbɔːl]', 'n.篮球', '1. We will play basketball tomorrow. 我们明天打篮球。 2. The basketball players are working out at the gym. 篮球运动员们正在体育馆进行训练。 3. We are going to play neither basketball nor volleyball. 我们既不将打篮球也不将打排球。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('haul', '[hɔːl]', 'v.拖；拉；拖运 v.（使船）改变方向 n.拖；拉；搬运', '1. They hauled the boat up the beach. 他们把船拖上岸。 2. It cost him no end of time and groans to haul his wounded leg behind him; 他拖着那条受伤的大腿往上爬，时不时地呻吟一声，速度非常慢。 3. So I won\'t have to haul you around all the time. 这样我就不用老是拉着你去这去那了。 4. Falumpasets haul battle wagons and the catapults of the Gungan Grand Army into the battlefield, and Boss Nass uses a decorated falumpaset as a ceremonial transport. 费隆帕斯特拖运刚耿大军的战车及投石机上战场，而那斯老大以一只装饰华丽的费隆帕斯特做为典礼上用的交通工具。 5. It is a long haul to drive across the country. 开车越过这个国家，是一段艰苦的长途旅行。', '名词: hauler 过去式: hauled 过去分词: hauled 现在分词: hauling 第三人称单数: hauls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('communication', '[kəˌmjuːnɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.交流；通讯；传达；通信；沟通', '1. Most important of all, computers create wide communication around the world. 最重要的是,计算机在世界范围内建立了广泛的交流。 2. Being able to hold a conversation does not necessarily mean having effective communication. 能够对话并不意味着在进行有效的交流。 3. This area has not been covered by the communication net. 这个地区还不在通讯网的覆盖之内。 4. The beach life-guards usually flag one another for communication. 海滨救生员通常用旗号传达讯息。', '形容词: communicational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('option', '[\'ɑːpʃn]', 'n.选择权；可选物 v.得到或获准进行选择', '1. He had no option but to agree. 他除了同意外别无选择。 2. I haven\'t much option in the matter. 在这件事情上我无可选择。 3. Make a list of the various options. 列出可供选择的项目。 4. He had optioned for a film several short stories about two policemen. 他为一部影片选择了几篇关于两位警察的短篇小说。', '过去式: optioned 过去分词: optioned 现在分词: optioning 第三人称单数: options');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('information', '[ˌɪnfər\'meɪʃn]', 'n.信息；情报；资料；通知', '1. They were unable to provide much information. 他们不能提供很多信息。 2. We are able to get the information we need from the Internet. 我们可以从网上得到我们需要的信息。 3. The police haven\'t got enough information to catch the criminal. 警方还未得到可捉拿这个罪犯的足够情报。 4. He gave us a very interesting piece of information. 他给我们一份很有趣的资料。', '形容词: informational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('job', '[dʒɑːb]', 'n.工作；职业；职位；(一项)任务；活儿；职责；犯罪行为；物件', '1. I do get a job in a travel agency. 我真的在旅行社找了份工作。 2. He lost his job during the great depression. 他在大萧条时期失业了。 3. His present job seemed to be a blind alley. 他现在的职业看来没什么前途。 4. Why are you out of job for such a long time? 你为何失业这么久?', '过去式: jobbed 过去分词: jobbed 现在分词: jobbing 第三人称单数: jobs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alloy', '[\'ælɔɪ]', 'n.合金 vt.使成合金；使降低，贬损；掺以杂质 vi.有合金能力', '1. Brass is an alloy of copper and zinc. 黄铜是铜和锌的合金。 2. The alloy has excellent thermal stability. 合金有极好的温度稳定性。 3. Mercy should alloy our stern resentment. 宽容会缓和积怨。 4. Nothing occurred to alloy our happiness. 未发生任何损害我们幸福的事情。', '过去式: alloyed 过去分词: alloyed 现在分词: alloying 第三人称单数: alloys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('agency', '[\'eɪdʒənsi]', 'n.代理；代理处；政府机构', '1. I hope we can see eye to eye about the other terms of the agency then. 我希望到那时候我们能在代理协议的其他条款上能取得一致意见。 2. I got this job through an employment agency. 我通过职业介绍所找到了这份工作。 3. They resigned their child to an adoption agency. 他们把自己的孩子交给了一家收养机构。 4. The agent is the person who works for a government agency in secret. 特工人员是为政府部门秘密工作的人。', '名词复数: agencies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('farewell', '[ˌfer\'wel]', 'int.再会；别了 n.告别 adj.告别的', '1. Farewell until we meet again! 下次再见！ 2. Farewell! I hope we meet again soon. 别了！希望很快我们能再见面。 3. I bade farewell to my parents. 我告别了双亲。 4. It\'s time to say our farewells. 是我们该告辞的时候了。 5. She had a fervent farewell speech. 她发表了热情的告别演说。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bachelor', '[\'bætʃələr]', 'n.单身汉；学士', '1. You have the alternative of marrying or remaining a bachelor. 你可以结婚也可以仍做单身汉，任你选择。 2. He remained a bachelor all his life. 他终生未娶。 3. Are you a Bachelor of Arts? 你是文学学士吗？ 4. Bush graduated from Yale with a bachelor\'s degree in history in 1968, 布什1968年从耶鲁大学毕业，获历史学学士学位，', '名词: backelordom');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('penny', '[\'peni]', 'n.便士；【美】分', '1. I only have a few pennies with me. 我身上只有几个便士。 2. He said that he wouldn\'t lend me a penny. 他说过他一便士都不愿借给我。 3. He felt in his pocket for a penny. 他在口袋里摸索着找一个便士。 4. He keeps track of every penny he spend. 他记录他花掉的每一分钱。', '名词复数: pennies/pence');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('be', '[bi]', 'v.有；在；是；到达；拜访', '1. It is necessary that he be sent there at once. 有必要马上派他到那里去。 2. There will be rain in all parts of the country. 全国各地将有雨。 3. A successful businessman must be aggressive. 一个成功的商人必须有进取心。 4. She has been in her room for hours. 她在自己的房间里待了几个小时。', '第三人称单数: is 现在分词: being 过去式: was/were 过去分词: been');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wet', '[wet]', 'adj.湿的；雨天的；懦弱的 n.潮气；雨天 vt.(使)弄湿', '1. The paper has wrinkled where it got wet. 这张纸湿的地方起皱褶了。 2. You will get wet if you go out without an umbrella. 你出门不带伞会被淋湿的。 3. A bicycle cape will protect you in wet weather. 自行车雨披可以使你在雨天骑车也不致淋湿。 4. The crowds packed into the cinema on a wet day. 一大群人在雨天挤进了电影院。 5. I stepped in a puddle and got my foot wet. 我踏进一个小水潭，把脚弄湿了。', '比较级: wetter 最高级: wettest 过去式: wet/wetted 过去分词: wet/wetted 现在分词: wetting 第三人称单数: wets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sprinkle', '[\'sprɪŋkl]', 'v.洒；撒；下稀疏小雨 n.少量散布的屑状物', '1. He sprinkled vinegar on his fish and chips. 他把醋洒在鱼和薯条上。 2. He wanted to tell her to sprinkle the floor. 他想告诉她在地上洒点水。 3. Sprinkle a little salt on the rice. 在米饭上撒点盐。 4. Grate the cheese and sprinkle it over the tomatoes. 把干酪磨碎撒在西红柿上。 5. We covered the cakes with chocolate sprinkles. 我们给蛋糕洒上巧克力末。', '过去式: sprinkled 过去分词: sprinkled 现在分词: sprinkling 第三人称单数: sprinkles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('presumably', '[prɪ\'zuːməbli]', 'adv.大概；据推测；可能', '1. Presumably the bad weather has delayed the flight. 大概恶劣的天气使飞机误点了。 2. She is aware of the difficulties, presumably? 她对这些困难大概了解吧? 3. They have been purposefully perforated, presumably to be strung together. 而且还被有目的的穿孔了，据推测是为了把它们穿起来。 4. Presumably Bryant would only leave to a team that offered an equal or greater chance to win a title. 据推测，布莱恩特将只会留在一个能提供给他平等或更大机会赢得总冠军的一支球队。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oil', '[ɔɪl]', 'n.油；油画颜料；奉承话 v.涂油；溶化；加油', '1. The country is rich in oil and coal. 这个国家石油和煤的资源丰富。 2. You should oil the sewing machine to stop the squeaking. 你应该给缝纫机上点油，以免发出轧轧声。 3. He slicks his hair down with oil every day. 他每天搽油把头梳得光溜溜的。 4. I prefer to use watercolors rather than oil paints. 我比较喜欢用水彩而不是油画颜料画画。 5. The man whom I bought it from told me to oil it. 我向他买这样东西的那个人告诉我要给它上油。', '过去式: oiled 过去分词: oiled 现在分词: oiling 第三人称单数: oils');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('premise', '[\'premɪs]', 'n.前提 vt.预述；提论；假设', '1. I wonder whether the whole premise is right. 我怀疑整个前提是否正确。 2. We must act on the premise that the worst can happen. 我们必须在可能发生最坏事态的前提下行动。 3. British justice works on the premise that an accused person is innocent until he\'s proved guilty. 英国司法运作的前提是被告在被证明有罪之前是清白的。 4. You had better premise your argument with a little historical knowledge. 你最好引述一些历史知识作为你立论的前提。', '过去式: premised 过去分词: premised 现在分词: premising 第三人称单数: premises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('certify', '[\'sɜːrtɪfaɪ]', 'vt.证明；保证；证实；颁发证书', '1. I certify that this is a true copy. 我证明这是真副本。 2. I certify that he has received your money. 我证明他已经收到了你的钱。 3. Can you certify for his ability as a teacher? 你可以保证他能胜任老师的工作吗? 4. I certify on my honour that he is innocent. 我用人格担保他是清白无辜的。', '名词: certifier 过去式: certified 过去分词: certified 现在分词: certifying 第三人称单数: certifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pleasant', '[\'pleznt]', 'adj.令人愉快的；讨人欢喜的；舒适的；宜人的', '1. We spent many hours in a pleasant conversation. 我们畅谈了好几个小时。 2. This tiny flower gives forth a pleasant fragrance. 这种小花散发出一种令人愉快的香味。 3. Peter is so pleasant that everyone likes him. 彼得很风趣，人人都喜欢他。 4. He has a pleasant manner, and finds it easy to make friends. 他态度随和,因此很容易交到朋友。', '副词: pleasantly 比较级: pleasanter 最高级: pleasantest 名词: pleasantness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('think', '[θɪŋk]', 'v.认为；想；记起；考虑 n.想', '1. I think you are very brave. 我认为你非常勇敢。 2. Women used to think they were on the shelf at 30. 过去女人一到30岁就认为是过了结婚年龄。 3. If you want to make money you\'ve got to think money. 你要是想赚钱，脑子里就得想著钱。 4. He was trying to think what to do. 他在努力想办法。 5. I will have a think and let you know tomorrow. 我要好好想一想，明天告诉你。', '过去式: thought 过去分词: thought 现在分词: thinking 第三人称单数: thinks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('news', '[nuːz]', 'n.新闻；消息', '1. Have you read the news about the election? 你看了关于选举的新闻了吗？ 2. She tapped out a news story on the typewriter. 她用打字机打出一篇新闻报道。 3. I heard it on the 7 o\'clock news. 我在七点钟的新闻报道中听到了这则消息。 4. I haven\'t heard any news from my son lately. 我最近没听到我儿子的任何音讯。', '形容词: newsless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hospital', '[\'hɑːspɪtl]', 'n.医院', '1. When I left the hospital I was completely cured. 出院时，我已经完全痊愈了。 2. If you go to a private hospital you must pay. 如果你去一家私立医院就诊，你得付费。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('piano', '[pi\'ɑnoʊ]', 'n.钢琴 adj.轻柔的 adv.轻柔地', '1. He is a wizard at playing the piano. 他是个钢琴奇才。 2. She is learning to play the piano. 她在学弹钢琴。', '名词复数: pianos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gum', '[ɡʌm]', 'n.牙床；树胶；齿龈；粘性物质 v.搞砸；用牙床嚼；以树胶粘合', '1. He has some sore swellings on his gum. 他牙床肿痛。 2. The tree is covered with gum. 树上涂有树胶。 3. Heart attack patients usually have gum diseases! 心脏病患者通常患有齿龈疾病。 4. We can stick these pictures into the book with gum. 我们可用胶水把这几张画粘贴在书里。 5. You\'ll gum up the jobs if you do it this way. 你这样做会把事情搞砸。', '过去式: gummed 过去分词: gummed 现在分词: gumming 第三人称单数: gums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('decent', '[\'diːsnt]', 'adj.相当好的；体面的；适当的；正派的', '1. Are there any decent restaurants around here? 这附近有没有好的餐厅？ 2. He dreamed of living in decent conditions. 他梦想着过体面的生活。 3. The lack of decent public transport is a great disadvantage. 没有适当的公共交通工具是很不方便的。 4. John and his wife Leah are very decent people. 约翰是他的妻子丽亚都是非常正派的人。', '副词: decently 名词: decentness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lower', '[\'loʊər]', 'adj.低的；下级的；下层的 v.降低；减弱；跌落', '1. The publisher paid his hacks low. 出版商付给他雇佣的文人很低的费用。 2. He because of bashful but low head. 他因羞愧而低下了头。 3. The lower level is subordinate to the higher level. 下级服从上级。 4. He belongs to the lower middle class. 他来自中产阶级下层。 5. Don\'t lower yourself by asking him for help. 不要向他求助以免降低身分。', '副词: loweringly 异体字: lour 过去式: lowered/loured 过去分词: lowered/loured 现在分词: lowering/louring 第三人称单数: lowers/lours');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flap', '[flæp]', 'n.拍打；拍打声；片状垂悬物；副翼；<口>不安 v.拍打；鼓翼而飞', '1. A flap from the tail of the whale upset the boat. 鲸尾轻轻一拍便把小船打翻了。 2. The flap of the birds drew the attention of a cat. 这群鸟不停地振翅吸引了一只猫的注意力。 3. I licked the flap of the envelope and sealed it. 我舔了舔信封盖口,把它封好。 4. I flap the flies away but soon they fly back. 我把苍蝇赶走，但一会儿又飞回来了。', '过去式: flapped 过去分词: flapped 现在分词: flapping 第三人称单数: flaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('serve', '[sɜːrv]', 'v.服务；侍候；担任；可作 ... 用；度过；对待 n.发球', '1. We must serve the people heart and soul. 我们必须全心全意地为人民服务。 2. The waiter is serving another customer. 侍应正侍候另一位客人。 3. He served as a naval officer during the war. 战时他在海军当军官。 4. The large box in his room can serve as a desk too. 他房间里的那只大箱子也可以当桌子用。 5. Whose serve is it now? 该谁发球了？', '过去式: served 过去分词: served 现在分词: serving 第三人称单数: serves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assistant', '[ə\'sɪstənt]', 'n.助手，助理，助教；【化】（用于染色的）助剂 adj.副的；辅助的', '1. The Prime Minister came to visit our country in the company of his assistant. 首相在其助手陪同下访问我国。 2. Wang wore two hats as chief of marketing research and assistant head of sales. 王先生身兼两职,是市场调查部主任,也是营销部副主任。 3. She is an assistant teacher in our school. 她是我们学校的助理教员。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('warehouse', '[\'werhaʊs]', 'n.仓库 vt.存入仓库', '1. They stored their goods in a warehouse. 他们把货物储存在一个仓库里。 2. They operate three factories and a huge warehouse. 他们经营三家工厂和一个大仓库。 3. If necessary, please warehouse the goods. 如有必要，请将该货存入仓库。', '名词: warehouser 过去式: warehoused 过去分词: warehoused 现在分词: warehousing 第三人称单数: warehouses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cater', '[\'keɪtər]', 'v.提供饮食及服务；迎合；满足', '1. Our hotel also caters for weddings and parties. 本饭店也承办婚礼、宴会。 2. These hotels cater especially to foreign tourists. 这些旅馆专门为外国游客提供服务。 3. They only publish novels which cater to the mass market. 他们只出版迎合大众市场的小说。 4. TV programs must cater for many different tastes. 电视节目必须满足观众的不同爱好。', '名词: caterer 过去式: catered 过去分词: catered 现在分词: catering 第三人称单数: caters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shower', '[\'ʃaʊər]', 'n.淋浴；阵雨；送礼会；(大量)涌泻 v.冲(淋浴)；下(阵雨)；倾注', '1. She is taking a shower. 她正在洗淋浴。 2. Scattered showers are expected this afternoon. 预料今天下午有零星阵雨。 3. The weatherman predict shower this afternoon. 气象预告员说,今天下午有阵雨。 4. The neighbors held a bridal shower for the girl. 邻居为姑娘举行了一个准新娘送礼会。 5. I always shower after getting up. 起床后我总是洗个淋浴。', '形容词: showery 过去式: showered 过去分词: showered 现在分词: showering 第三人称单数: showers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('distance', '[\'dɪstəns]', 'n.距离；路程；远方 vt.与 ... 保持距离；把(对手)甩在后面', '1. He judged the distance to a nicety. 他判断距离很正确。 2. My house is four miles distance from the sea. 我家离海四英里。 3. We can see a windmill in the distance. 我们可以望见远处有架风车。 4. A lighthouse was winking in the far distance. 一座灯塔正在远处闪烁。 5. A more appropriate stance would be for the leader to distance itself from the com-petitors. 作为领导者，一个较正确的姿态是在自己和对手之间，拉开距离 。', '过去式: distanced 过去分词: distanced 现在分词: distancing 第三人称单数: distances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thrift', '[θrɪft]', 'n.节俭；节约', '1. Industry and thrift favor success. 勤劳和节俭有助于成功。 2. Thrift is engrafted in his character. 他已经节俭成性。 3. Thrift has become the prevailing practice. 节约成风。 4. A businessman must wed.efficiency to thrift. 企业家必须于效率兴节约相结合。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('certainty', '[\'sɜːrtnti]', 'n.确定；确实的事情', '1. I can say with certainty that this is true. 我可以很确定地说这是真实的。 2. Too great certainty destroys certainty itself. 过于确定就会破坏确定本身。', '名词复数: certainties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('employment', '[ɪm\'plɔɪmənt]', 'n.职业；雇用；使用', '1. I got this job through an employment agency. 我通过职业介绍所找到了这份工作。 2. He enrolled with an employment agency for a secretary. 他在职业介绍所登记要当秘书。 3. He left his home to look for employment. 他离家去找职业。 4. His employment is that of a bookbinder. 他的职业是装订工。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lift', '[lɪft]', 'vt.举起；运送；偷窃；升高；还清；取消 vi.提升 n.举起；提升；电梯；搭便车；帮助；载货量；扒窃', '1. He was too weak even to lift his hand. 他虚弱得连手都抬不起来。 2. The helicopter lifted the entire team to the meet. 直升飞机把全队空运到运动会现场 3. She was caught lifting make-up from the supermarket. 她在超级市场偷窃化妆品时被捉住了。（《牛津高阶英汉双解词典》） 4. The good news lifted my spirits. 这好消息使我精神大振。 5. They want to lift the rate of enjoyment too. 他们还想提升快乐率。 6. With a graceful lift of her hand, she dismissed him. 她轻盈地一抬手把他打发走了。', '形容词: liftable 名词: lifter 过去式: lifted 过去分词: lifted 现在分词: lifting 第三人称单数: lifts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assumption', '[ə\'sʌmpʃn]', 'n.假定；设想；担任(职责等)；假装', '1. The project was predicated on the assumption that the economy was expanding. 这一计划是以经济发展的设想为依据的。 2. The theory is based on a series of wrong assumptions. 这一理论是以一系列错误的设想为依据的。 3. His assumption of power was welcomed by everyone. 他的当权为大家所欢迎。 4. He talked with an assumption of ease. 他装出从容的样子说话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grip', '[ɡrɪp]', 'n.紧握；手提包；了解；手柄 vt.吸引；紧抓', '1. The eagle seized its prey in a tenacious grip. 鹰将捕获物紧紧抓住。 2. The child would not let go his grip on Tom. 这孩子紧紧地抓住汤姆不放。 3. He kept a firm grip on his children. 他对小孩管得很严。 4. It is a leather grip. 这是一个皮制手提包。 5. The audience were gripped by the play. 这群观众被这部戏剧吸引住了。', '副词: grippingly 名词: gripper 过去式: gripped 过去分词: gripped 现在分词: gripping 第三人称单数: grips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('access', '[\'ækses]', 'n.入口；通道 n.接近(的机会)；使用之权 vt.进入；(电脑)存取', '1. This is the only means of access to the building. 这是进入这栋楼的唯一入口。 2. The avalanche cut off the access to the mountain village. 雪崩切断了进入山村的通道。 3. The only access to that building is along the track. 到那座大楼的唯一通道就是沿这条小路走。 4. Only high officials have access to the president. 只有高级官员才可以接近总统。 5. An error occurred when we tried to access the inventory database. 当我们试图进入存货数据库时，屏幕上显示出现了错误。', '过去式: accessed 过去分词: accessed 现在分词: accessing 第三人称单数: accesses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trolley', '[\'trɑːli]', 'n.手推车；<美>电车', '1. He rolled the trolley across the room. 他推着手推车穿过房间。 2. Just stay here with the baggage on the trolley. 你就待在这儿看管手推车上的行李。 3. Oil the trolley, and then it will turn more freely. 给手推车加点油，这样它就能自由运转了。 4. These suitcases are too heavy to carry; we need a trolley. 这些衣箱太沉了，我们需要一辆小手推车。', '过去式: trolleyed/trollied 过去分词: trolleyed/trollied 现在分词: trolleying/trollying 第三人称单数: trolleys/trollies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outfit', '[\'aʊtfɪt]', 'n.配备；用具；机构 vt.配备；供应 vi.得到装备', '1. She was prancing along in her new outfit. 她穿著全套新衣服神气活现地走著。 2. Such an outfit would be a useful addition to my wardrobe. 在我的服装中添置这一套会有用的。 3. The company will provide the sports outfits for all the players. 这家公司将为所有运动员提供全套运动服装。 4. His father bought a ski outfit for him on his birthday. 他父亲在他生日那天给他买了一套滑雪用具。 5. The mountain climbers were outfitted with the latest equipment. 登山者用最新的设备装备起来。 6. We will outfit two days before sailing. 我们将在出航前两天整装。', '名词: outfitter 过去式: outfitted 过去分词: outfitted 现在分词: outfitting 第三人称单数: outfits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('moderate', '[\'mɑːdərət]', 'adj.适度的；温和的；稳健的；中等的 v.节制；使 ... 稳定，使 ... 缓和 n.稳健的人', '1. Moderate exercise will be of benefit to you. 适度运动对你有益。 2. Corn plants grow well in moderate weather. 谷类植物在温和气候中生长繁盛。 3. He holds moderate opinions. 他的意见稳健不偏激。 4. The team enjoyed only moderate success last season. 上个赛季，这个球队只取得了中等成绩。 5. She moderated her enthusiasm deliberately . 她有意地节制了自己的热情。 6. He is a moderate. 他是个稳健的人', '副词: moderately 名词: moderateness 过去式: moderated 过去分词: moderated 现在分词: moderating 第三人称单数: moderates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('federal', '[\'fedərəl]', 'adj.联邦制的；联邦政府的；同盟的 n.联邦主义者；同盟盟友', '1. Switzerland is a federal republic. 瑞士是联邦制的共和国。 2. Expenditures by the Federal Government have been steadily pared. 联邦政府的开支正在逐渐削减。', '副词: federally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('claw', '[klɔː]', 'n.爪；钳；螯；爪状物 v.抓；撕', '1. Cats have sharp claws. 猫有锋利的爪子。 2. A hen\'s claw has three toes. 母鸡的脚爪有三个脚趾。 3. The editor got his claws into the opposition in a vicious editorial. 那个编辑在一篇社论中恶毒地攻击了反对派。 4. His face was badly clawed. 他的脸给抓坏了。', '形容词: clawed 过去式: clawed 过去分词: clawed 现在分词: clawing 第三人称单数: claws');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('performance', '[pər\'fɔːrməns]', 'n.表演；实行；表现；履行；性能；本事；业绩', '1. His performance gripped the audience. 他的表演深深地吸引住观众。 2. Proposal is easier than performance. 建议容易实行难。 3. His good performance in school does great credit to his mother. 他在学校的优良表现为他母亲带来极大的荣誉。 4. He was assiduous in performance of duty. 他勤勉地履行职责。', '动词: perform');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('football', '[\'fʊtbɔːl]', 'n.<英>足球；<美>橄榄球', '1. Football and hockey players wear shoulder pads. 足球和曲棍球球员都戴垫肩。 2. The local schools formed a football league. 当地几所学校组建了足球联合会。 3. He is on the college football team. 他是大学橄榄球队的队员。 4. Touch football is a favorite time killer. 打触身式橄榄球是一种人们喜爱的消遣。', '名词: footballer');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lot', '[lɑːt]', 'n.许多；大量；抽签；签；命运；一块地；拍卖品；一类或一些(人或物)；批；套；份儿 adv.很；非常 v.划分；分配', '1. It takes a lot of labor to build a railway. 修筑一条铁路要花费许多劳动力。 2. She had a lot of problems to contend with. 她有许多问题要解决。 3. The flood did a lot of damage to the crops. 洪水毁坏了大量农作物。 4. This firm prints a lot of musical and sports books. 这家公司出版了大量的音乐和体育书籍。 5. I\'m feeling a lot better today. 我今天身体好多了.', '过去式: lotted 过去分词: lotted 现在分词: lotting 第三人称单数: lots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('centre', '[\'sentər]', 'n.中心；集中点 v.居中；使集中 =center<美> adj.中心的；中央的', '1. That new shopping centre is a real eyesore. 那个新的购物中心真是难看极了。 2. The new library was built in the centre of the campus. 新图书馆建在校园的中心。 3. Children like to be the centre of attention. 儿童喜欢引人注意. 4. Please centre the subheads. 小标题一律居中。 5. Pupils are the centre parts of one\'s eyes. 瞳孔是人眼的中心部位。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('normal', '[\'nɔːrml]', 'adj.正常的；正规的；精神健全的 n.常态；标准', '1. Everything is absolutely normal. 一切完全正常。 2. She refused to conform to the normal social conventions. 她拒绝遵从正常的社会习俗。 3. People who commit crimes like that aren\'t normal. 犯这种罪的人心理都不正常. 4. It was several days before the floodwater sank and life returned to normal. 过了几天洪水才退,生活恢复了正常。', '副词: normally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('save', '[seɪv]', 'v.救；节省；保存 n.救援，救助', '1. The doctor managed to save his life. 医生救了他的命。 2. Children should learn to save. 孩子们应学会储蓄。 3. I lent him my bike in order that he could save time. 我把自行车借给他,以便他能节省一些时间。 4. Save your strength for the hard work you\'ll have to do later. 留着点儿劲儿,你一会儿还得干重活儿呢。', '形容词: savable 名词: saver 过去式: saved 过去分词: saved 现在分词: saving 第三人称单数: saves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('afternoon', '[ˌæftər\'nuːn]', 'n.下午', '1. Good afternoon! 下午好！ 2. She could knit up a baby\'s coatee in an afternoon. 她一个下午就能编结好一件婴孩的紧身短上衣。 3. I met him in a hot and breathless afternoon. 我是在一个又闷又热的下午遇到他的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('experience', '[ɪk\'spɪriəns]', 'n.经验；经历 v.经历；体验；感受', '1. He has had no previous experience in this kind of job. 他从前没有做这种工作的经验。 2. I know from my own experience how difficult the work can be. 从我自己的经验我明白这项工作会有多难。 3. I had a singular experience in Africa. 我在非洲时有过一次奇特的经历。 4. The shipwreck was a harrowing experience. 那次船难是一个惨痛的经历。 5. You will experience a dream of fantasy. 你将会经历一个梦幻之旅。', '名词: experiencer 过去式: experienced 过去分词: experienced 现在分词: experiencing 第三人称单数: experiences');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('graphic', '[\'ɡræfɪk]', 'adj.生动的；图表的 n.图表', '1. The general gave a graphic account of the battle. 将军对战斗作了生动的描述。 2. He was a man of many words and many graphic gestures. 他是一个话多的人，还不停比划着生动的手势。 3. The newspaper article gave a graphic description of the earthquake. 报纸文章生动地描述了地震的情况。 4. The principal kept a graphic record of school attendance. 校长用图表记录学生的出席率。 5. Please help me to make a graphic. 请帮我做份图表。', '副词: graphically 名词: graphicness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loyal', '[\'lɔɪəl]', 'adj.忠诚的；忠心的', '1. A loyal man stands by his friends in weal or woe. 一个忠诚的人无论祸福都会支持他的朋友。 2. We are loyal to our motherland. 我们忠于祖国。 3. I may say in all sincerity that you have been my most loyal friend. 我可以非常真诚地说，你一直是我最忠实的朋友。 4. The royal destroyer employs lots of loyal employees. 皇家驱逐舰雇佣了很多忠心的雇员。', '副词: loyally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tire', '[\'taɪər]', 'n.轮胎；金属圈 v.使疲倦；厌烦；劳累', '1. There is no tread on the tire - you should put on a new one. 这条轮胎已经磨平了，你应该换一条新的。 2. The tires of this car don\'t have enough air in them. 这辆汽车的轮胎气不足了。 3. I never tire of reading Shakespeare. 我对莎士比亚的作品百读不厌。 4. The ceremony was short so as not to tire them. 仪式很简短，以免使他们疲劳。', '过去式: tired 过去分词: tired 现在分词: tiring 第三人称单数: tires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ashore', '[ə\'ʃɔːr]', 'adv.在岸上；上岸', '1. They have been ashore for two hours. 他们上岸已经两个小时了。 2. Until then, the bears stranded ashore will have company. 在那之前，徘徊于岸上的北极熊也会有访客。 3. The oil comes ashore in floating patches that stain the coral black and gray. 浮在海面上的片片油污漂到岸上，把珊瑚都染成了黑灰色。 4. He managed to swim ashore. 他设法向岸边游过去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ingredient', '[ɪn\'ɡriːdiənt]', 'n.成分；原料；配料；因素', '1. Coconut is a basic ingredient for many curries. 椰子是多种咖喱菜的基本成分。 2. Mix all the ingredients in a bowl. 将原料放在盆里调匀. 3. There is a list of ingredients on the side of the packet. 包装袋的边上印有所含配料表。 4. Humor is an effective ingredient of a speech. 幽默是演讲中效果极佳的一个因素。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('highway', '[\'haɪweɪ]', 'n.公路；(水陆空)直接航线或路线', '1. A four-lane highway connects the two cities. 一条四车道的公路连接这两个城市。 2. This narrow highway should be broadened. 这条狭窄的公路应该加宽。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('give', '[ɡɪv]', 'v.给；赠予；送；捐助；提供；供给；举行；弯曲 n.弹性', '1. Would you please give me a piece of paper? 能给我一张纸吗？ 2. He give me a box in which to keep the toy. 他给了我一个装着玩具的盒子。 3. He gives generously to the poor. 他慷慨地施舍给穷人。 4. I\'m giving all my friends books for Christmas. 我在圣诞节要向所有的朋友赠书。 5. This rope has too much give in it. 这条绳子弹性太大.', '过去式: gave 过去分词: given 现在分词: giving 第三人称单数: gives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bake', '[beɪk]', 'v.烤；烘焙；烘干；<非正式>灼热', '1. The bread is baking in the oven. 烤箱里正在烤面包。 2. I will bake Tracy several buns now. 我现在要为特蕾西烤几个小面包。 3. We bake bread and cake in an oven. 我们用烤箱烘面包与糕点。 4. In some places, bricks are still baked in the sun. 有些地方仍使用在太阳下晒干砖块的方法。', '过去式: baked 过去分词: baked 现在分词: baking 第三人称单数: bakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cake', '[keɪk]', 'n.蛋糕；块状物', '1. He passed me one fifth of the cake. 他递给我五分之一个蛋糕。 2. I often bake chocolate cake by myself. 我喜欢自己培巧克力蛋糕。', '过去式: caked 过去分词: caked 现在分词: caking 第三人称单数: cakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sight', '[saɪt]', 'n.视力；看见；视线；景物 v.瞄准；看见；观测', '1. I\'m having laser treatment to improve my sight. 我正在接受激光治疗来提高我的视力。 2. The captain ordered us to shoot any strangers on sight. 船长命令我们凡是看见的陌生人都要将其枪毙。 3. The train is still in sight. 火车仍在视线内。 4. It didn\'t take long before I lost sight of the plane. 没多久,飞机就在我的视线中消失了。 5. The hunter sighted carefully before firing his gun. 猎人射击前仔细瞄准。', '过去式: sighted 过去分词: sighted 现在分词: sighting 第三人称单数: sights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conviction', '[kən\'vɪkʃn]', 'n.坚信；定罪；信服', '1. I have the conviction that he is right. 我深信他是对的。 2. She holds deep religious convictions. 她有深刻的宗教信仰。 3. This was his third conviction. 这是他第三次被判罪。 4. They have no previous convictions. 他们没有前科。', '形容词: convictional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plaster', '[\'plæstər]', 'n.石膏；灰泥；膏药 v.涂以灰泥；敷以膏药；使 ... 平', '1. His broken leg was encased in plaster. 他折的腿打上了石膏。 2. They closed the cracks in the wall with plaster. 他们用石膏把墙上的裂缝填满了。 3. This plaster may crack when it dries. 这种灰泥变干时可能会龟裂。 4. The plaster had started to come away from the wall. 灰泥已经开始从墙上脱落。 5. Will it take long to plaster the ceiling? 把天花板涂上灰泥要花很长时间吗?', '形容词: plastery 名词: plasterer 过去式: plastered 过去分词: plastered 现在分词: plastering 第三人称单数: plasters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('happy', '[\'hæpi]', 'adj.高兴的；幸福的；幸运的；乐意的', '1. I am so happy to hear of your engagement. 听到你订婚我很高兴。 2. This has been the happiest day of my life. 这是我生活中最快乐的一天。 3. I wish you a very happy future. 我祝你有非常幸福的未来。 4. They had a very happy marriage. 他们有个幸福美满的婚姻。', '副词: happily 比较级: happier 最高级: happiest 名词: happiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('church', '[tʃɜːrtʃ]', 'n.礼拜仪式；教堂；基督教徒 adj.教堂的 v.把 ... 带到教堂接受某种宗教仪式', '1. Church begins at 9 o\' clock. 礼拜仪式9点开始。 2. Christians go to church on Sundays. 基督教徒每个星期日到教堂去做礼拜。 3. Everyone in church knelt in prayer. 教堂里每个人都跪着祈祷。 4. I\'m just going to the church to see the priest. 我正要去教堂去见见牧师。 5. She loves church music. 她喜爱教堂音乐。', '过去式: churched 过去分词: churched 现在分词: churching 第三人称单数: churches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anonymous', '[ə\'nɑːnɪməs]', 'adj.匿名的；无名的；没特色的', '1. It is unpleasant to receive anonymous letters. 接到匿名信是一件令人不快的事。 2. The man was arrested after an anonymous tip-off. 有人匿名举报后，那个人被抓了起来。 3. The author chooses to remain anonymous. 作者愿不署名。 4. An anonymous author wrote this book. 这本书出自无名氏之手。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bottle', '[\'bɑːtl]', 'n.瓶子 vt.抑制；把 ... 装入瓶内', '1. Why don\'t we crack open a bottle of champagne to celebrate? 我们何不开瓶香槟酒庆祝一下呢？ 2. Try not to bottle up your emotions. 尽量不要压抑自己的情感。 3. Tell us what\'s worrying you; don\'t bottle it up! 把心中的烦恼告诉我们,不要把它闷在心里！ 4. Do you bottle your fruit or freeze it? 你是把水果装在罐里保存呢，还是冷冻起来保存？', '名词: bottler 过去式: bottled 过去分词: bottled 现在分词: bottling 第三人称单数: bottles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('forty', '[\'fɔːrti]', 'num.四十 adj.四十 pron.四十(个；只 ... )', '1. They managed to squash forty people into the bus. 那辆公共汽车好不容易塞进了四十个人。 2. He reigned over the country for forty years. 他统治了这个国家四十年。', '名词复数: forties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('device', '[dɪ\'vaɪs]', 'n.装置；设备；策略；设计', '1. The data logger device has been fitted to ship\'s engine room. 数字记录仪装置已安装在船只的机舱里。 2. The printer is the most commonly used output device after the monitor. 打印机是除显示器外最常用的输出设备。 3. It\'s just a tactical device to get over a split in their own Party. 这不过是他的想要克服党内分歧的一种策略。 4. Sending advertising by mail is very successful as a marketing device. 邮寄广告作为一种营销策略是非常成功的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weary', '[\'wɪri]', 'adj.疲倦的；厌烦的 v.疲倦；厌烦；生厌', '1. After many hours in the saddle he was very weary. 骑马骑了几个小时后，他非常疲倦。 2. I feel weary after such a long journey. 经过这么长时间的旅行后，我觉得很累。 3. We all grew weary of his long-winded speech. 我们对他冗长的发言都感到很厌烦。 4. He began to be weary of the research work. 他开始对研究工作感到厌烦。 5. The long walk completely wearied us. 这麽长的路走得我们疲惫不堪。', '副词: wearily 比较级: wearier 最高级: weariest 名词: weariness 过去式: wearied 过去分词: wearied 现在分词: wearying 第三人称单数: wearies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anyway', '[\'eniweɪ]', 'adv.不管怎样；无论如何', '1. Anyway she said what was in her mind. 不管怎样，她说了心里话。。 2. He reflected that the quality of the instruments was good anyway. 他寻思，不管怎样，这些乐器的质量还是不错的。 3. I don\'t think they need help, but I think I should offer anyway. 我认为他们无须帮助，不过我想我应有所表示。 4. Anyway, he must have eaten a lot because now he is fat. 无论如何，他一定吃了很多东西，因为现在他胖了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hitherto', '[ˌhɪðər\'tuː]', 'adv.到目前为止；迄今', '1. Hitherto, this is the advanced method. 到目前为止，这是先进的方法。 2. Hitherto he had experienced no great success in his attempt. 到目前为止，他的这种尝试还没有取得任何重大的成功。 3. For hitherto though I have lost all my time. 迄今我虽然失去了全部的时日。 4. I had hitherto continued to board with Godfrey. 迄今我仍在戈费雷处用膳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fifteen', '[ˌfɪf\'tiːn]', 'num.十五', '1. He has fifteen workers in his employ. 他雇佣的工人有十五名。 2. Fifteen separate republics comprised the Soviet Union. 苏联由十五个加盟共和国组成。 3. I caught six trout in fifteen minutes. 我在十五分钟内钓到了六条鳟鱼。 4. Most students in this class are fifteen. 这个班的大多数孩子都十五岁。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fee', '[fiː]', 'n.费用；酬金', '1. She charged only a nominal fee for her work. 她为所做的工作只收取象征性的费用。 2. The doctor\'s fee was higher than we expected. 这位医生的收费比我们预料的高。 3. Tickets are issued only against payment of the full fee. 只有付讫全费才可将票发出。 4. I\'m afraid I can\'t afford the doctor\'s fee. 恐怕我付不起给医生的酬金。', '过去式: feed 过去分词: feed 现在分词: feeing 第三人称单数: fees');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('withdraw', '[wɪð\'drɔː]', 'vt.撤回；取回；撤退；提款 vi.撤退；退缩；走开', '1. In view of members reservation and request for further information, the Administration agreed to withdraw the item. 鉴于委员有所保留,并要求取得进一步资料,政府当局同意撤回该项目。 2. He wanted to withdraw his name from the guest list. 他想从客人名单中撤出自己的名字。 3. I\'d like to withdraw some money from my account. 我想从户头里提出一些钱。 4. The troops have been withdrawn from the danger area. 部队已经撤出危险地带。 5. Tell the men to withdraw from their new position. 告诉那些人从新的阵地上撤出。', '形容词: withdrawable 名词: withdrawer 过去式: withdrew 过去分词: withdrawn 现在分词: withdrawing 第三人称单数: withdraws');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('entertain', '[ˌentər\'teɪn]', 'v.娱乐；使有兴趣；招待；考虑；抱有；容纳', '1. We were all entertained by his humorous stories. 他的幽默故事使我们大家都很开心。 2. A teacher should entertain as well as teach. 教师不仅要教书，也要激起学生的兴趣。 3. I like to entertain friends with music and refreshments at home. 我喜欢在家里用音乐和茶点招待朋友。 4. It was futile to entertain such a question. 考虑这样一个问题是没有用的。', '名词: entertainer 过去式: entertained 过去分词: entertained 现在分词: entertaining 第三人称单数: entertains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thin', '[θɪn]', 'adj.薄的；瘦的；稀的', '1. The ice on the pond is too thin for skating. 池塘上的冰面太薄了，不能滑冰。 2. His face is thin and very tanned. 他的面孔瘦削,晒得黑黑的。 3. This string is too thin, I need a thicker piece. 这根绳子太细了,我需要一根粗些的。 4. Boil down the soup until it gets thicker. I don\'t like thin soup. 把汤熬浓,我不喜欢稀汤。', '形容词: thinnish 副词: thinly 比较级: thinner 最高级: thinnest 名词: thinness 过去式: thinned 过去分词: thinned 现在分词: thinning 第三人称单数: thins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expensive', '[ɪk\'spensɪv]', 'adj.昂贵的；高价的', '1. The dress is too expensive for me to buy. 那衣服太昂贵，我买不起。 2. A cheaper camera is not always inferior to a more expensive one. 廉价照相机的质量并总不比昂贵的差。 3. This set of crystal wine cups is very expensive. 这套水晶玻璃酒杯非常昂贵。 4. The overhead costs are ridiculously expensive. 日常开支太高了。', '副词: expensively 名词: expensiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('picnic', '[\'pɪknɪk]', 'n.野餐；愉快的时间；猪脊肉 vi.野餐', '1. Let\'s go for a picnic by the riverside. 我们到河边野餐去吧。 2. We had a lot of fun at the picnic on the beach. 我们在海滩上野餐，趣味无穷。 3. It\'s no picnic having to look after 6 small children all day. 整天照看6个小孩子可不是轻松愉快的事。 4. Their family often picnics in the woods. 他们一家常在树林里野餐。', '形容词: picnicky 名词: picnicker 过去式: picnicked 过去分词: picnicked 现在分词: picnicking 第三人称单数: picnics');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reproach', '[rɪ\'proʊtʃ]', 'n.责备；耻辱 v.责备；申斥', '1. His reply sounded to me like a reproach. 他的回答在我听来象是责备。 2. Her behaviour was above/beyond reproach. 她的行为是无可指责的。 3. His reply sounded to her like a reproach. 他的回答在她听来像是责备。 4. A coward is a reproach to an army. 懦夫是军队的耻辱。 5. She reproached her husband for having forgotten their wedding anniversary. 她责怪丈夫忘了他们的结婚周年纪念日。', '形容词: reproachable 副词: reproachably 名词: reproachableness 过去式: reproached 过去分词: reproached 现在分词: reproaching 第三人称单数: reproaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('approval', '[ə\'pruːvl]', 'n.同意；批准；认可；赞同', '1. The proposal was accepted with unanimous approval. 全体一致通过了那项建议。 2. We should submit our plans to the council for approval. 我们应该向理事会提交计划以求批准。 3. Your approval gives me much gratification. 承蒙认可，我非常高兴。 4. He showed his approval by shaking my hands. 他和我握手，表示赞成。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dry', '[draɪ]', 'adj.干的；干燥的；干旱的；口渴的；枯燥的 v.（使）变干', '1. The soil is too dry for planting. 土太干了，不能种东西。 2. After these dry days, everyone hopes for rain. 干燥的天气之后，人人都希望下雨。 3. We should prepare for more dry weather. 我们应该为更干旱的天气做准备。 4. I always feel dry in this hot weather. 遇到这种炎热天气我总感到口渴。 5. The bread will dry out if it is left on the table. 不要把面包放在桌上，它会变干的。', '副词: dryly 比较级: drier/dryer 最高级: driest/dryest 名词: dryness 名词复数: drys 过去式: dried 过去分词: dried 现在分词: drying 第三人称单数: dries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('operational', '[ˌɑːpə\'reɪʃənl]', 'adj.操作的；运作的；可用的；作战的', '1. The New Attack Submarine is designed for multi-mission operations and enhanced operational flexibility. 新攻击潜艇拥有多任务操作的设计，提高了操作的灵活性。 2. He reported to the committee on routine operational matters. 他向委员会汇报日常的手术事宜。 3. The new system became operational in March. 新系统三月份可用。 4. His operational plans have been completely upset. 他们的作战计划完全被打乱了。', '副词: operationally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bullet', '[\'bʊlɪt]', 'n.子弹；弹丸', '1. He grunted as the bullet hit him. 子弹击中他时他疼得哼了出来。 2. A bullet whizzed past my ear. 一颗子弹嗖的一声从我耳边飞过。 3. The bullet went clean through his arm. 子弹穿过他的手臂。 4. The bullet hit him in the chest. 子弹击中了他的胸膛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('occasional', '[ə\'keɪʒənl]', 'adj.偶然的；临时的；不时的', '1. He\'s someone I have an occasional chat and joke with. 我偶然跟他闲聊，一起说笑话。 2. An occasional outburst of anger creates wrinkles on the face. 一次愤怒的偶然爆发会在脸部产生皱纹。 3. All in a occasional chance, he got the out-of-print book in a secondhand bookstore. 纯粹由于偶然的机会，他在一家二手书店里找到了那本绝版的书. 4. He is only an occasional workman. 他只是个临时雇工。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lest', '[lest]', 'conj.惟恐；以免；担心', '1. They spoke in whispers lest they should be heard. 他们低声说话，唯恐被别人听见。 2. He took a flashlight lest it should get dark before he returned. 为了预防回来以前天就黑了，所以他带着手电筒。 3. I got up early lest I should miss the train. 我早起以免错过了火车。 4. We talked in a low voice lest we should wake the baby up. 我们小声说话以免吵醒婴儿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('voyage', '[\'vɔɪɪdʒ]', 'n.航行；旅程 v.航行；旅行', '1. This is the virgin voyage of the ship. 这是这艘船的处女航。 2. The ship hit heavy fog on its voyage. 船在航行时碰上了大雾。 3. She went on a long sea voyage. 她乘船在海上长途旅行。 4. Once the voyage comes to an end. 旅程结束之际。 5. My dream is to voyage around the world in a hot air balloon. 我的梦想是乘着热气球周游世界。', '名词: voyager 过去式: voyaged 过去分词: voyaged 现在分词: voyaging 第三人称单数: voyages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strap', '[stræp]', 'n.皮带；带子 vt.(用带子)捆扎；(用带子)抽打', '1. The strap had been fretted away. 皮带已经被磨损了。 2. Her camera strap has broken. 她的照相机吊带断了。 3. A safety strap is used to prevent falling. 安全带是用来防止滑落的。 4. A watch strap holds a watch on your wrist. 表带把手表系在手腕上。 5. Experienced travelers strap in without waiting to be asked. 有经验的旅客一就座便自动系好安全带。', '过去式: strapped 过去分词: strapped 现在分词: strapping 第三人称单数: straps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flavor', '[\'fleɪvə]', 'n.风味；特殊的滋味；风格；调味品 vt.加调料于...；给...添加情趣', '1. The course has a distinctive Italian flavor. 这道菜很有意大利餐的风味。 2. I don\'t like the flavor of onion. 我不喜欢洋葱的味道。 3. These works have a strong flavor of rural life. 这些作品散发着浓郁的乡土气息。 4. She flavored the fish with sugar and vinegar. 她用糖和醋给鱼调味。', '形容词: flavorless 名词: flavorer 过去式: flavored 过去分词: flavored 现在分词: flavoring 第三人称单数: flavors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('someone', '[\'sʌmwʌn]', 'pron.某人；有人', '1. The camera filmed someone leaping into the house. 照相机拍到了某人突然跳入那房子的画面。 2. Someone tried to poison our dog. 有人想毒杀我们的狗。 3. I seem to hear someone knocking at the door. 我好像听到有人在敲门。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fate', '[feɪt]', 'n.命运；宿命', '1. Are we the puppets of fate? 我们是听任命运摆布的傀儡吗？ 2. She wondered what fate had in store for her next. 她不知道以后等待她的将是什么命运。 3. The fate is waits for the matchmaker? 宿命就是等待月老吗？ 4. Theirs is a fate perennially suffered by intellectuals. 他们的命运其实是知识分子长久以来承受的宿命。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sequence', '[\'siːkwəns]', 'n.顺序；连续；次序；一系列 vt.按顺序排好', '1. We will deal with events in historical sequence. 我们将按照历史上的先后顺序研究这些事件。 2. She made a sequence of dance movements. 她做了一个连续的舞蹈动作。 3. He described the events of that day in sequence. 他按先后次序描述了那一天发生的种种事件。 4. A sequence of murders had prompted the police to actions. 一连串的谋杀迫使警方不得不采取行动。 5. Please sequence the names in alphabetical order. 请按字母顺序排列好名单。', '过去式: sequenced 过去分词: sequenced 现在分词: sequencing 第三人称单数: sequences');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('recorder', '[rɪ\'kɔːrdər]', 'n.记录员；记录器（录音机等） n.（英国某些市镇的）首席法官；市法院法官 n.竖笛', '1. He works as a recorder in the city court. 他在市法院当记录员。 2. The recorder chalked it up as soon as the athlete beat a new record. 运动员一打破记录，记录员就立即公布。 3. Use Recorder to record keystrokes or mouse actions to play back later. 用记录器记录击键或鼠标行为，以备后来播放。 4. According to the record, the cord was the oldest recorder the people could afford. 据记载，绳子是人们用得起的最古老的记录器。 5. Like most musical children, Tom first played the recorder. 象大多数喜欢音乐的孩子一样，汤姆第一次使用八孔竖笛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clock', '[klɑːk]', 'n.时钟 v.计时；打卡', '1. The clock shows half past two. 时钟的针指著两点半。 2. This clock has outlasted several owners. 这座时钟的寿命比它的几个主人的寿命都长。 3. The silence was succeeded by the striking of a clock. 时钟鸣响声打破了寂静。 4. There must be something wrong with my clock. 我的钟一定是坏了。 5. Workers usually clock off at 5.30. 工人们通常在5时30分下班。', '名词: clocker 过去式: clocked 过去分词: clocked 现在分词: clocking 第三人称单数: clocks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('effort', '[\'efərt]', 'n.努力；努力的成果', '1. They are making every effort to decrease the production cost. 他们正尽力减少生产成本。 2. All my efforts were fruitless. 我所有的努力都白费了。', '形容词: effortful 副词: effortfully');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('so', '[soʊ]', 'adv.那么；这样；如此 adj.真的；非常 pron.这样 conj.因此；所以；以便', '1. He felt pity for a man suffering so much. 他对那个受过那么多痛苦的人感到同情。 2. How could you be so stupid as to believe him? 你怎么这么笨竟相信他的话？ 3. Stand with your arms out, so. 两臂伸开站著，就这样。 4. I gave you a map so you wouldn\'t get lost. 我给你一张地图，这样你就不会迷路了。 5. So I really enjoyed my tea just now. 所以刚才的茶点我真的很欣赏。 6. These glasses are very expensive, so please be careful with them. 这些玻璃杯十分昂贵,因此请小心些。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ghost', '[ɡoʊst]', 'n.幽灵；鬼魂 n.[计]美国赛门铁克公司旗下的硬盘备份还原工具', '1. The teeny tiny ghost flies away. 小小幽灵飞走了。 2. The ghost has been laid and will not return to haunt you again. 那鬼魂已经祛除，不会再回来缠著你了。 3. He was shaking with fright as if he had seen a ghost. 他吓得直哆嗦，就好像看见了鬼一样。 4. I can\'t have seen a ghost it must have been imagination. 我看到的不可能是鬼－－一定是幻想的东西吧。', '形容词: ghosty 过去式: ghosted 过去分词: ghosted 现在分词: ghosting 第三人称单数: ghosts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('initial', '[ɪ\'nɪʃl]', 'n.(词)首字母 adj.开始的；最初的；字首的 vt.签姓名的首字母于', '1. This is a letter paper personalized with his initials. 这是一张有他姓名首字母的信纸。 2. After the initial cheers,the noise of the crowd began to die away as the group started playing. 开始的欢呼声结束以后，乐队开始演奏，人们的喧闹声也随之逐渐消失。 3. We are through the initial testing period. 我们通过了最初的考试阶段 4. The word “hour” is pronounced without an initial aspirate. hour一词的首字母h不发送气音。 5. She initialed a handkerchief and gave it to that young man. 她在手帕上绣上姓名的首字母，把它送给了那个年轻人。', '副词: initially 名词: initialness 过去式: initialed/initialled 过去分词: initialed/initialled 现在分词: initialing/initialling 第三人称单数: initials/initials');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mammal', '[\'mæml]', 'n.哺乳动物', '1. The bat is the only mammal that can fly. 蝙蝠是唯一会飞的哺乳动物。 2. Is a meadow more complex than a mammal brain? 草地较之哺乳动物的大脑更复杂吗？', '形容词: mammalian');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('philosopher', '[fə\'lɑːsəfər]', 'n.哲学家；思想家；达观者', '1. He represented himself as a philosopher. 他声称自己是哲学家。 2. The philosopher speculated about time and space. 这位哲学家在思索时间和空间问题。 3. Mencius was a famous ancient Chinese philosopher. 孟子是中国古代的着名思想家。 4. I do not agree, for instance, that he is a philosopher, or a thinker. 譬如，我不同意他自以为是哲学家或思想家这种看法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('film', '[fɪlm]', 'n.电影；薄膜；胶卷 vt.把 ... 拍成电影；给 ... 覆上一薄层；拍照片 vi.变朦胧；拍摄电影', '1. He made a film about Egypt. 他拍了一部关于埃及的电影。 2. I\'m going to see a film this Sunday. 在本星期天,我打算看一场电影。 3. There was a film of grease on the water. 水上有一层油。 4. He bought two rolls of film for the camera. 他给照相机买了两卷胶卷。 5. It took them six weeks to film the documentary. 他们拍摄这部纪录片用了六个星期。 6. The window filmed over with moisture. 窗子上覆盖着水汽模糊不清', '过去式: filmed 过去分词: filmed 现在分词: filming 第三人称单数: films');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('replace', '[rɪ\'pleɪs]', 'vt.取代；替换；放回原处；偿还', '1. Nothing can replace a mother\'s love. 什么都无法取代母爱。 2. We\'ve replaced the old adding machine with a computer. 我们用电脑取代了老式的加法计算器。 3. The coach decided to replace player No. 8 with No. 3. 教练决定让3号替换8号。 4. He replaced the book in the shelf. 他把书放回到书架上。', '形容词: replaceable 名词: replacer 过去式: replaced 过去分词: replaced 现在分词: replacing 第三人称单数: replaces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pity', '[\'pɪti]', 'n.怜悯；同情；遗憾；可惜 v.同情；怜悯', '1. The old lady often takes pity on small animals. 那位老太太常常怜悯小动物。 2. He remained unmoved by her entreaties for pity. 他未因她恳求怜悯而动心。 3. We took pity on the homeless girl and took her into our house. 我们同情这个无家可归的女孩，让她住进了我们的屋子里。 4. I helped her out of love, not out of pity. 我帮助她是出于爱，而不是出于同情。 5. I pity anyone who has to feed a family on such a low income. 我同情任何需要以如此微薄的收入养活全家的人。', '副词: pityingly 名词复数: pities 过去式: pitied 过去分词: pitied 现在分词: pitying 第三人称单数: pities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('harvest', '[\'hɑːrvɪst]', 'n.收成；收获；收割；成果；后果 v.收获；收割', '1. It happened that the harvest was bad in 1988. 碰巧一九八八年的收成很糟。 2. The fine summer harvest was not easily come by. 夏季的好收成不是容易得来的。 3. The harvest has been safely gathered in. 庄稼已妥善收获完毕。 4. We are all very busy because it\'s the harvest time. 因为现在是收获期，所以我们都非常忙。 5. Farmers harvest their crops in fall. 农民秋天收获庄稼。', '形容词: harvestable 名词: harvestability 过去式: harvested 过去分词: harvested 现在分词: harvesting 第三人称单数: harvests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('museum', '[mju\'ziːəm]', 'n.博物馆；展览馆', '1. The museum has many immemorial cultural relics. 该博物馆收藏了很多极其古老的文物。 2. The museum displays the specimen of ancient Chinese porcelain. 这个博物馆展出中国古瓷器标本。 3. Flashes are not allowed to be used in this museum. 这个博物馆里不准使用闪光灯。 4. We found a Picasso in the museum. 我们在展览馆发现了一张毕加索画的画。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scenery', '[\'siːnəri]', 'n.风景；背景；布景', '1. The scenery is beautiful beyond description. 那里的风光美得难以描述。 2. We admired the splendor of the mountain scenery. 我们赞赏着壮丽的山景。 3. He asked us to lash the scenery up with rope. 他要我们用绳子把舞台背景绑起来。 4. The scenery in the play is beautiful, but the actors get in front of it. 那出戏的背景很美，可惜演员们站在前面给挡住了。', '名词复数: sceneries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('emphasize', '[\'emfəsaɪz]', 'vt.强调；着重；使突出', '1. He emphasized the importance of careful driving. 他强调小心驾驶的重要性。 2. We cannot emphasize too much the importance of learning English. 我们再怎样强调学英文的重要性也不为过。 3. Which word should I emphasize? 我应该重读哪个词? 4. I would like to emphasize that we are ready to meet the management at any time. 我想着重指出，我们愿意在任何时候与管理部门会谈。', '过去式: emphasized 过去分词: emphasized 现在分词: emphasizing 第三人称单数: emphasizes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('alphabet', '[\'ælfəbet]', 'n.字母表；基本原理(元素)；符号系统', '1. C comes after B in the alphabet. 在字母表中C接在B后面。 2. There are 26 letters in the English alphabet. 英语字母表中有26个字母。 3. The first letter in the English Alphabet is A. 英语字母表中的第一个字母是A。 4. he said the space is the most important character in the alphabet. 他说空格是系统符号里最重要的字符。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('invalid', '[ɪn\'vælɪd]', 'adj.无效的；病弱的 n.病人；残疾者 vt.退役；遣送回家', '1. A passport that is out of date is invalid. 护照过期是无效的。 2. Unless a check is signed, it is invalid. 支票除非签了名，否则是无效的。 3. She looks after her invalid mother. 她照看病弱的母亲。 4. Nobody looks after the invalid. 没人照顾这个病人。 5. He was invalided out of the army because of the wounds he received. 他因负伤而退役。', '副词: invalidly 名词: invalidity 过去式: invalided 过去分词: invalided 现在分词: invaliding 第三人称单数: invalids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('essay', '[\'eseɪ]', 'n.论文；短评；散文；试图 vt.尝试', '1. This essay is admirable in all respects. 这篇文章在各方面都很值得欣赏。 2. I had turn over my essay to the professor. 我已经把论文交给教授了。 3. This essay represents a considerable improvement on your recent work. 这篇论文说明你最近的工作取得了相当大的改进。 4. The teacher geve an essay on his composition. 老师给他的作文做了一个短评。 5. He essayed to speak but was told to be quiet. 他试图发言,但主席让他不要讲话。', '名词: essayer 过去式: essayed 过去分词: essayed 现在分词: essaying 第三人称单数: essays');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('set', '[set]', 'v.放置；设定；确定；规定；调整；分配；(太阳)落下去；将（宝石）镶嵌到（某物）；配乐 n.集合；组合；日落；一套；一副；一局比赛；舞台；姿态；头发的定型 adj.规定的；固定的；不变的；做好准备的；固执的；不自然的', '1. He set aside the book and lit a cigarette. 他把书放置在一边,点燃了香烟。 2. How do we set the enrollment criteria? 我们如何设定录取标准? 3. We have set the date for the wedding. 我们已经确定了婚期。 4. We set a limit on the expenses of the trip. 我们规定了这次旅游的费用。 5. It may be a very simple or complicated set of instructions. 这个指令的集合可能非常简单，也可能十分复杂。 6. Please follow the set procedures when you use this product. 使用该产品时请遵循规定的步骤。', '过去式: set 过去分词: set 现在分词: setting 第三人称单数: sets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('apply', '[ə\'plaɪ]', 'vt.应用；涂；使专心从事 vi.申请；有关联', '1. We should not only know the theory but also how to apply it to practice. 我们不仅要知道理论，还要知道怎样把理论应用于实践。 2. The plastic coating is easy to be applied on any surface. 塑性涂料容易涂在任何表面上。 3. I am applying for a fellowship. 我在申请研究生奖学金。 4. Above terms shall apply unless otherwise mention. 除非另有说明书,上述条件一概适用。', '过去式: applied 过去分词: applied 现在分词: applying 第三人称单数: applies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gentleman', '[\'dʒentlmən]', 'n.绅士；先生；有教养的人', '1. The old gentleman had on a classic suit. 那位老年绅士穿著一套古朴的传统服装。 2. Please bring this gentleman a cup of coffee. 请给这位先生拿一杯咖啡。 3. I looked up at the gentleman in the clericals. 我抬头看著这位身穿教士服的先生。 4. A true gentleman is above envy, jealousy or vindictiveness. 一个真正有教养的人是没有妒忌猜疑或报复心的。', '形容词: gentlemanly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fault', '[fɔːlt]', 'n.缺点；故障；过错；[地]断层 v.找 ... 错误', '1. I like him despite his faults. 虽然他有很多缺点，我仍然喜欢他。 2. He has many faults, but vanity is not one of them. 他有很多缺点，但并没有虚荣心。 3. There is a fault in the electrical system. 电路系统出了故障。 4. It was not our fault that we were late. 这次迟到不是我们的错。 5. No one could fault his performance. 他的演出无懈可击.', '过去式: faulted 过去分词: faulted 现在分词: faulting 第三人称单数: faults');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('married', '[\'mærid]', 'adj.已婚的；婚姻的；密切结合的 n.已婚者', '1. He sank upon the fact that he was married. 他隐瞒了已婚的事实。 2. Married officers get extra allowances. 已婚的军官有额外津贴。 3. Friends regarded Karen and Jeff as a shining example of a happily married couple. 朋友认为卡伦和杰夫是婚姻的光辉典范。 4. I have never been married and am still a virgin waiting until marriage. 我并未结过婚，依然保持着纯洁之身期盼婚姻的到来。 5. Of course, some of them had been married mostly before becoming rickshaw pullers or arriving in Chengdu, but the men seldom got married when they were rickshaw pullers. 不过，已婚者大多是在沦为拉车之前或者是来成都之前成的家，而拉车期间结婚的非常之稀少。', '名词复数: marrieds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sink', '[sɪŋk]', 'v.下沉；沉没；渗透；低落；变低；衰弱；（太阳）落下 n.水槽；沟渠；散热器；接收端', '1. Wood does not sink in water, it floats. 木头在水中不沉，而是漂在水面。 2. The boat will sink unless we bail out. 我们要不把积水清除掉，船就要沉了。 3. The ship was sunk by an enemy torpedo. 这艘船被敌人的鱼雷击沉了。 4. Rub the cream on your skin and let it sink in. 把这种软膏搽在皮肤上，让它渗进去。 5. The dirty dishes are in the sink. 那些脏盘子在洗涤槽内。', '形容词: sinkable 过去式: sank/sunk 过去分词: sunk 现在分词: sinking 第三人称单数: sinks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('zoo', '[zuː]', 'n.动物园；拥挤杂乱的地方', '1. He saw some amazing sights at the zoo. 他在动物园里看到一些珍禽异兽。 2. Did you see any elephants in the zoo last week? 上星期你在动物园里看到大象了吗？ 3. I\'ll meet you at the entrance of the zoo tomorrow. 明天我会在动物园的入口处和你见面。 4. Predictably, the mixed zone was a zoo. 正如所料，混合区里一片拥挤。', '名词复数: zoos');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('okay', '[oʊ\'keɪ]', 'adv. <表示同意或允许>好的； 可以； 行 adj. 好的 n. 同意 vt. 同意', '1. Okay Squirrel, you can play with us. 你可以和我们一起玩儿。 2. Is itl okay to stke in the office? 在办公室里抽烟可以吗？ 3. Okay, alright, I was sharp shooting. 行，好吧，我是锋利的射击。 4. Okay, let\'s bet fifty dollars on who wins. 行，拿五十块钱来打赌，看看到底谁赢。 5. Okay,I\'ll take that.No garnishes.Just meat,Okay? 好的，我就要那种，上面不放东西，只是肉而已，好吗？ 6. Don\'t come out of your hiding-place until I give you the okay. 得到我的同意你才能从躲藏的地方出来。 7. Don\'t come out of your hiding-place until I give you the okay. 得到我的同意你才能从躲藏的地方出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('text', '[tekst]', 'n.正文；文本；课文；原文 v.发短信', '1. The text is accompanied by illustrations. 正文附有插图。 2. It was edited from the original text. 这是根据原文本编译的。 3. Read the text first and then explain the new words. 先读课文，然后解释生词。 4. He studied Shakespeare\'s texts. 他学习了莎士比亚的原作。 5. Laura, will you text me the venue again? 劳拉,你能把聚会地点再给我发一次吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('agitate', '[\'ædʒɪteɪt]', 'v.煽动；搅动；焦虑', '1. They sent agents to agitate the local people. 他们派遣情报人员煽动当地的民众。 2. Agitate the mixture to dissolve the powder. 搅动混合物而使粉末溶化。 3. He was agitated about his wife\'s health. 他为他妻子的健康感到不安。 4. He became quite agitated when he was asked about his criminal past. 当问到他过去的犯罪历史时，他变得十分焦虑不安。', '形容词: agitative 副词: agitatedly 过去式: agitated 过去分词: agitated 现在分词: agitating 第三人称单数: agitates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('federation', '[ˌfedə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.联邦；联合；联盟', '1. United Federation of Planets incorporated. 星际联邦组成。 2. One of the states has seceded from the federation. 有一个州已从联邦中退出。 3. The small countries joined together into a federation. 小国联合起来组成一个联盟。 4. This Standard is prepared by China Federation of Power Enterprises. 本标准由中国电力企业联合会提出。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intricate', '[\'ɪntrɪkət]', 'adj.复杂的；难懂的', '1. It was an intricate and ingenious system. 这是一个复杂而精致的体系。 2. The prisoners designed the intricate escape. 囚犯们策划了那起周密的越狱事件。 3. Taiwan is a complex of intricate relationships. 台湾是个各种关系错综复杂的地方。 4. The situation seems to be intricate. 局势似乎错综复杂。', '副词: intricately 名词: intricateness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dean', '[diːn]', 'n.系主任；学院院长；教务长；(基督教)教长 Dean. n.迪安（人名）', '1. The dean returned in the late afternoon. 系主任是在傍晚时分回来的。 2. The dean cautioned him against being late. 系主任告诫他不要迟到。 3. Accompanied by the dean, they visited the hospital. 在院长的陪同下，他们参观了医院。 4. The dean assembled the students in the auditorium. 教务长把学生集合在礼堂里。 5. This was Torvill and Dean at their best. 这是托维尔和迪安的最隹表现。', '名词: deanship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reel', '[riːl]', 'v.卷；绕 v.眩晕；旋转；蹒跚 n.卷筒；线轴', '1. I put a new reel of film in my camera. 我一卷新胶卷装入照相机。 2. When you\'re sure that you have hooked the fish, reel in at once. 当你确信鱼儿已经上钩时，赶紧收卷钓线。 3. Help me to reel up this powerful fish. 帮我收绕钓线拉起这条大鱼。 4. He cast the line suddenly just like throw it into the water and then reel it back. 他把线突然抛出，就像扔进水中一样，然后把线绕回。 5. My head reeled with the facts and figures. 我的脑子被一堆事实和数据搞得一片混乱 6. The reel of film is not in the proper order. 电影胶片卷盘的顺序弄错了。', '形容词: reelable 名词: reeler 过去式: reeled 过去分词: reeled 现在分词: reeling 第三人称单数: reels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gun', '[ɡʌn]', 'n.枪；炮；节流阀 vt.枪击；打开节流阀 vi.用枪打猎', '1. The gun has a carry of 400 yards. 这枪的射程为四百码。 2. He was clubbed to death with a butt of a gun. 他是被人用枪托殴打致死的。 3. It\'s illegal to carry guns in our country. 在我们国家，携带枪支是违法的。 4. The soldier saw a gun jutting out from a bush. 那士兵看见一支枪从矮树丛伸出来。 5. I saw them gun down innocent women and children. 我看到他们枪杀无辜的妇女和儿童。', '过去式: gunned 过去分词: gunned 现在分词: gunning 第三人称单数: guns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pledge', '[pledʒ]', 'vt.发誓；保证；以 ... 抵押；向 ... 祝酒 n.保证；抵押；誓言；抵押品', '1. They pledged never to tell the secret. 他们发誓决不泄密。 2. We all had to pledge allegiance to the flag. 我们大家都得发誓忠于这面旗帜。 3. She pledged her support to us. 她保证支持我们。 4. I pledge myself to fulfil the promise I have made. 我保证实践自己的诺言。 5. And as we walk, we must make the pledge that we shall march ahead. 当我们行动时,我们必须保证勇往直前。', '过去式: pledged 过去分词: pledged 现在分词: pledging 第三人称单数: pledges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('medieval', '[ˌmedi\'iːvl]', 'adj.中世纪的', '1. Knighthood was an ideal in medieval Europe. 在中世纪的欧洲，成为骑士是理想。 2. The medieval town was fortified with a high wall and a deep moat. 这座中世纪的城市周围建有城墙和护城河。 3. This church is a classic example of medieval architecture. 这座教堂是中世纪建筑风格的典型实例。 4. The gallery is a treasure trove of medieval art. 这个画廊是中世纪艺术的宝库。', '副词: medievally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('influence', '[\'ɪnfluəns]', 'v.影响；感染；<美俚>在(饮料)中加烈酒 n.影响力；影响；权势；势力；有影响的人(或事物)', '1. Don\'t let me influence your decision. 不要让我影响你的决定。 2. The labour enthusiasm of the workers strongly influenced us. 工人们的劳动热情极大地感染了我们。 3. He makes a nice drink for women by influencing orange juice. 他在橘子汁里加了少量烈性酒即制成了适于女性的爽口饮料。 4. His influence is on the ebb. 他的影响力逐渐在衰退。', '形容词: influenceable 名词: influencer 过去式: influenced 过去分词: influenced 现在分词: influencing 第三人称单数: influences');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('postage', '[\'poʊstɪdʒ]', 'n.邮费；邮资已付邮戳', '1. It costs a pound, plus ten pence for postage. 这东西值一镑，另加邮费十便士。 2. What is the postage for an air letter? 寄一封航空信的邮费要多少？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('from', '[frəm]', 'prep.出自；来自；从( ... 起)', '1. He descended from a good family. 他出自名门。 2. From what author does this quotation come? 这一引文出自哪位作者? 3. Bitter words from you will only wound her. 出自你口中的尖刻话只会伤害她而已。 4. My answer seemed to come from the subconscious. 我的回答似乎出自下意识。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bruise', '[bruːz]', 'n.瘀青；擦伤；挫伤 vi.碰伤；擦伤 vt.使挫伤', '1. His face is a mass of bruise after the fight. 他打完架后脸上青一块紫一块的。 2. She is lucky to get off with just a few bruise. 她幸免于难,只是有几处擦伤。 3. She had a dilly of a bruise on her arm. 她手臂上有一块显眼的伤痕。 4. It can range from a minor Bruise or sprain to a skull fracture with Brain damage or a spinal-cord injury with paralysis. 其范围从小型挫伤或扭伤到大脑受损的头颅裂开或麻痹性脊椎伤害。 5. Soft fruit bruises easily. 细嫩的水果容易碰损。 6. She fell and bruised her knee. 她摔倒在地，膝盖上起了紫血块。', '过去式: bruised 过去分词: bruised 现在分词: bruising 第三人称单数: bruises');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('goods', '[ɡʊdz]', 'n.货物；商品；动产 n.罪证', '1. The goods were consigned to you by railway. 货物已由铁路托运到你处。 2. Please honor our arrangement by exchanging the damaged goods. 请遵守我们的协议，给我们调换损坏的货物。 3. Can the goods be refunded at your counter? 你们柜台的商品可以退吗？ 4. Our goods are second to none in the world market. 在国际市场上,我们的商品不亚于任何人。 5. The authorities have got the goods on us. 当局拿到了我们的罪证。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elevate', '[\'elɪveɪt]', 'vt.举起；提拔；素养提升；鼓舞 vi.变高', '1. They had the attempt to elevate Anderson to the presidency. 他们企图把安德逊抬上总统宝座。 2. He used a couple of bolsters to elevate his head. 他用两个垫枕垫头。 3. They had the attempt to elevate Anderson to the presidency. 他们企图把安德逊抬上总统宝座。 4. Reading good books elevates your mind. 阅读好书使人思想高尚。', '过去式: elevated 过去分词: elevated 现在分词: elevating 第三人称单数: elevates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('edge', '[edʒ]', 'n.边缘；优势；边；刀口 vt.给 ... 加上边；缓慢横过；使锋利 vi.徐徐前进', '1. Look out! You could fall off the edge here! 小心!你会从这边缘掉下的。 2. New houses have mushroomed on the edge of the town. 城市边缘的新建房屋犹如雨后春笋。 3. In the second half of the game, the home team got the edge on the visitors and kept it. 比赛下半场,主队比客队略占上风,并把这一优势保持到终场。 4. Because of the high exchange rate, our products have lost their competitive edge. 由于汇率很高, 我们的产品失去了竞争优势。 5. She lost a handkerchief edged with blue. 她丢了一块镶蓝边的手绢。 6. Unemployment will edge up, but not by much. 失业率将缓慢上升，但增幅不是很大。', '形容词: edgeless 过去式: edged 过去分词: edged 现在分词: edging 第三人称单数: edges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crane', '[kreɪn]', 'n.鹤；起重机 v.起吊；伸长(脖子)；犹豫', '1. A crane and a crow had made a league on oath. 鹤和乌鸦宣誓结盟。 2. The crane was not happy with the peacock. 对于孔雀的炫耀，鹤不太高兴。 3. The crane soared high into the sky. 鹤展翅飞上云天。 4. The driver slewed the crane round. 司机把吊车转了过来。 5. They crane up building material. 他们以起重机举起建筑材料。', '过去式: craned 过去分词: craned 现在分词: craning 第三人称单数: cranes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gate', '[ɡeɪt]', 'n.大门；登机门；出入口；门票收入；<古>道路；<方>方式 v.<英>惩罚(禁止学生离校)；解雇 suf.常表示政治丑闻', '1. There are soldiers on guard at the gate. 大门口有士兵在守卫。 2. The gate is too narrow for a car. 大门太窄，汽车进不去。 3. The carriage passed through the palace gate. 马车进入了宫殿的大门。 4. Passengers for Madrid, gate number two. 去马德里的乘客，二号登机门。', '过去式: gated 过去分词: gated 现在分词: gating 第三人称单数: gates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('decade', '[\'dekeɪd]', 'n.十年', '1. Prices have risen steadily during the past decade. 在过去十年里，物价一直在上涨。 2. Several decades have elapsed since I graduated from the college. 我大学毕业已数十年了。 3. I believed that this struggle is going to go on and it might well be decided in the next decade. 我相信这一对抗还将会持续下去，并可能在下一个十年中得出结果。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('humanity', '[hjuː\'mænəti]', 'n.人类；人性；人道；慈爱；(复)人文学科', '1. Such a man is a stain to humanity. 这种人是人类的耻辱。 2. How can you turn aside from suffering humanity? 面对受苦受难的人类，你怎么能毫无同情心呢？ 3. Humanity is a mixture of good and bad qualities. 人性是善与恶的混合体. 4. He treated the prisoners with humanity. 他人道地对待俘虏。', '名词复数: humanities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('golf', '[ɡɑːlf]', 'n.高尔夫球 vi.打高尔夫球', '1. Let\'s play a round of golf. 我们打一场高尔夫球吧。 2. I have a special liking for golf. 我特别喜欢高尔夫球运动。 3. He won the golf match by two shots. 他以两杆的成绩赢得了这场高尔夫球赛。 4. Now he\'s getting towards retirement age he\'s started playing golf. 他因接近退休年龄，就打起高尔夫球来了。 5. He plays golf nearly every weekend. 他差不多每个周末都打高尔夫球。', '名词: golfer 过去式: golfed 过去分词: golfed 现在分词: golfing 第三人称单数: golfs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('circus', '[\'sɜːrkəs]', 'n.马戏团；马戏表演；竞技场；广场', '1. He performs riding stunts in the circus. 他在马戏团表演骑马绝技。 2. The circus placarded the city with advertisements. 马戏团满城张贴广告。 3. The fascinations of the circus are endless. 马戏表演非常吸引人。 4. The Roman circus was used for chariot and horse races. 罗马竞技场是用来举行敞篷双轮马车竞赛和赛马比赛的。', '形容词: circusy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('link', '[lɪŋk]', 'v.联系；连接 n.环；联系；节', '1. Television stations around the world are linked by satellite. 全世界的电视台通过卫星联系一起。 2. The road links all the new towns. 这条路把所有的新城镇都连接起来了。 3. He detached a link from a chain. 他从链子上拆下一个链环。 4. Is there a link between smoking and lung disease? 吸烟与肺部疾病之间有关系吗？', '名词: linker 过去式: linked 过去分词: linked 现在分词: linking 第三人称单数: links');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jolly', '[\'dʒɑːli]', 'adj.愉快的；快乐的 v.恭维；哄；开玩笑；戏虐 adv.非常；极为 n.（尤英）欢乐；欢庆 （复数jollies）娱乐，乐趣', '1. We had a jolly time during the winter holidays. 我们在寒假里过得很愉快。 2. They are making a jolly life of it. 他们生活得非常愉快。 3. Some indeed have a jolly life, others simply don\'t. 有些人的确有着欢乐的生活，但其他的人却没有。 4. They jollied the little girl into going with them. 他们哄得那女孩跟他们一起去。 5. He is a jolly good man. 他是一个大好人。 6. Some indeed have a jolly life, others simply don\'t. 有些人的确有着欢乐的生活，但其他的人却没有。', '副词: jollily 比较级: jollier 最高级: jolliest 名词: jolliness 名词复数: jollies 过去式: jollied 过去分词: jollied 现在分词: jollying 第三人称单数: jollies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('appetite', '[\'æpɪtaɪt]', 'n.食欲；嗜好；欲望', '1. She is suffering from lack of appetite. 她食欲不振。 2. The long walk has given me a good appetite. 走了长路使我食欲大振。 3. Mary has no appetite for hard work. 玛丽不想干艰苦的工作。 4. I have to make an effort to work up an appetite for reading. 我得努力使自己产生天天想读书的愿望。', '形容词: appetitive');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('response', '[rɪ\'spɑːns]', 'n.反应；回答；响应；答复', '1. The tax cuts produced a favourable response from the public. 税额削减受到了公众的欢迎. 2. I\'m sorry; the correct response is B. 不好意思,正确回答应该是B。 3. There was an enthusiastic response to my suggestions. 我的提议得到了热情的响应。 4. 他提出指控后迅即得到答复。 他提出指控後迅即得到答覆.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('conventional', '[kən\'venʃənl]', 'adj.传统的；惯例的；常规的', '1. Her book is a hilarious send-up of a conventional spy story. 她写的书用的是取笑传统侦探小说的笔法，令人捧腹。 2. According to conventional wisdom, voters usually make their choice on the basis of domestic issues. 按一般人在这些问题上的看法，选民常常着眼于国内问题来选择候选人。 3. After a conventional opening remarks, he made a brilliant speech. 在一个常规的开场白后,他做了个很精彩的演讲。 4. I can never get a girl like that with conventional methods. 我用寻常套路可永远也得不到这样的女孩。', '副词: conventionally 名词: conventionalism');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('probe', '[proʊb]', 'n.调查；查究；探针；探测器 v.用探针测；探测；详细调查', '1. They launched a probe into the disappearance of government funds. 他们发起了对政府资金流失一事的调查. 2. Pressure on the industry was building even before the latest probe. 事实上,在最近的调查之前,压力就已经在这个行业聚集。 3. The image sent back by the probe is very clear. 探针传回的图像非常清晰。 4. The brain surgeon asked the nurse to pass him a probe. 脑外科医生要护士将探针递给他。 5. The doctor will probe your stomach with a camera. 医生会用带摄像头的胃镜检查你的胃。', '副词: probingly 名词: prober 过去式: probed 过去分词: probed 现在分词: probing 第三人称单数: probes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overflow', '[ˌoʊvər\'floʊ]', 'v.泛滥；溢出；充满；洋溢 n.泛滥；溢值；剩出', '1. We must harness the rivers which overflow annually. 我们必须治理那些每年泛滥的河流。 2. The river overflowed its banks. 河水漫过了两岸。 3. The crowd overflowed the auditorium. 人群挤得礼堂无法容纳。 4. Her heart was overflowing with joy. 她的心里洋溢着喜悦。 5. Put a bowl underneath to catch the overflow. 把盆放在下面接住溢出物。', '过去式: overflowed 过去分词: overflowed 现在分词: overflowing 第三人称单数: overflows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obvious', '[\'ɑːbviəs]', 'adj.明显的；显然的', '1. It is obvious that she is very clever. 很明显，她挺聪明。 2. The embassy is an obvious target for terrorist attacks. 大使馆是恐怖分子攻击的明显目标。 3. The merits of the scheme are quite obvious. 该计画的可取之处是相当明显的。 4. All great truths are obvious truths. But no all obvious truths are great truths. 所有伟大的真理都是显而易见的事实,但并非所有显而易见的事实都是伟大的真理。', '副词: obviously 名词: obviousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('silver', '[\'sɪlvər]', 'n.银币；银器；银；银灰色 adj.银的；银色的 vt.镀银于；使 ... 成银色', '1. He had some silver in his pocket. 他口袋里有些银币。 2. Acid had pitted the surface of the silver. 酸把银器的表面腐蚀了。 3. His black hair was threaded with silver. 他的黑发中夹杂着银发。 4. This board was cast in bronze not in silver. 这个牌匾是铜铸的,不是银制的。 5. He found the chest to contain silver coins. 他发现那囗箱子装着银币。 6. He silvered a mirror. 他给镜子镀上了一层银。', '过去式: silvered 过去分词: silvered 现在分词: silvering 第三人称单数: silvers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wallet', '[\'wɑːlɪt]', 'n.皮夹；钱包', '1. She placed the receipt in her wallet. 她把收条放到皮夹子里了。 2. I lost my wallet yesterday. 我昨天丢了钱包。 3. My wallet has disappeared from the table. 我放在桌子上的钱包不见了。 4. The wallet was just under his nose, but he didn\'t see it. 钱包就在他眼前，可他没看见。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('heal', '[hiːl]', 'vt.治愈；使恢复健康；使和解 vi.痊愈', '1. Time heals most pains. 时间会消除很多痛苦。 2. The medicine and rest will soon heal your wound. 药物治疗和休息会使你的伤口很快愈合。 3. The holy man healed them of their sickness. 那位神职人员治好了他们的疾病。 4. Nothing could heal the rupture between he and his father. 没有什么可以弥合他和父亲之间的裂痕。 5. The terrible wound took a long time to heal. 这重伤费了很长时间才痊愈。', '形容词: healable 过去式: healed 过去分词: healed 现在分词: healing 第三人称单数: heals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('director', '[də\'rektər]', 'n.董事；经理；导演；主管，总监；指挥者', '1. The board nominated him as the new director. 董事会指定他为新董事。 2. Her career culminated in her appointment as director. 她一生事业的顶峰是当上董事。 3. I wouldn\'t advise you to go against the director. 我反对你和经理对着干。 4. He has a lot of pull with the managing director. 他对总经理有很大的影响力。', '名词: directorship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mould', '[moʊld]', 'n.形状；模子；气质；霉菌；土 v.模压；塑造；长霉', '1. Her fingers went over the mould of his face, over his features. 她的手指反复感知着他的脸型,他的特征。 2. The metal in the mould hardened into shape. 模子里的金属硬化成形。 3. He is a hero of the mould of Tung Tsun-jui. 他是董存瑞式的英雄。 4. He doesn\'t fit (into) the traditional mould of a university professor. 他没有大学教授那种传统的气质。 5. Wet the clay a bit more before you start to mould it. 把泥再弄湿点再动手塑造。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('possibly', '[\'pɑːsəbli]', 'adv.可能地；也许', '1. It is a parsimonious representation of a possibly complex thing. 这就是以简约来代表可能地复杂的事情。 2. Possibly because it\'s an electric razor. 也许是因为那是电动剃刀吧？ 3. He is possibly the most selfish man in the town. 他也许是镇上最自私的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('specialist', '[\'speʃəlɪst]', 'n.专家；专科医生；专食性动物', '1. We profit from the work of the specialist. 我们从专家的工作中得到益处。 2. The provision of specialist teachers is being increased. 配备专业教员的人数有所增加。 3. He is a plastic surgery specialist. 他是个整形外科医生。 4. Her mother is an eye specialist. 她母亲是眼科专家。', '形容词: specialistic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('energetic', '[ˌenər\'dʒetɪk]', 'adj.精力旺盛的；有力的；能量的', '1. His son is an energetic child. 他的儿子是个精力旺盛的孩子。 2. He seems an energetic person. 他似乎是一个精力充沛的人。 3. Her wiry athletic body seems energetic. 她瘦长结实的身体看上去精力充沛。 4. We should give energetic support to agriculture. 我们要大力支援农业。', '副词: energetically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feeling', '[\'fiːlɪŋ]', 'n.感觉；知觉；气氛；鉴赏力；反感 adj.有感情的；富于同情心的；含情脉脉的 （复）feelings：感情.', '1. I have a feeling that we are being followed. 我有种感觉我们正被人跟踪。 2. The feeling deepened with the passing of the years. 这种感觉一年一年地加深了。 3. He had no movement or feeling below his navel. 肚脐以下没有知觉，也不能活动。 4. I\'ve lost all feeling in the left arm. 我左臂完全失去了知觉。 5. He is not a mere lump of clay but a feeling creature. 他不仅具有血肉之躯而且是一个有感情的人。', '副词: feelingly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('salute', '[sə\'luːt]', 'v.行礼；致意；问候 n.致敬；敬礼；欢迎', '1. We salute the flag everyday at school. 我们在学校每天向国旗行礼。 2. This ignoramus failed to salute me. 这个蠢汉看见我不行礼。 3. They saluted each other by raising their hats. 他们举起帽子互相致意。 4. Shanghai people salute guests and friends from all over the world. 上海人民向海内外宾朋致意。', '名词: saluter 过去式: saluted 过去分词: saluted 现在分词: saluting 第三人称单数: salutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cord', '[kɔːrd]', 'n.细绳；索；纽带', '1. He tied the package with a cord. 他用绳子把包裹扎紧。 2. The dancer could kick over a cord four feet from the ground. 这位舞蹈家能把脚举到离地4英尺的绳索上面。 3. His mouth was taped, his hands and feet bound with curtain cord. 他的嘴上粘着胶布，手脚给窗帘拉索捆着。 4. Cindy and her fiance think of their letter as cord of love. 辛迪和她未婚夫把他俩的来往书信看作爱情的纽带。', '名词: corder 过去式: corded 过去分词: corded 现在分词: cording 第三人称单数: cords');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nod', '[nɑːd]', 'v.点头；打盹；（使）摆动 n.点头；同意', '1. She nodded when she passed me in the street. 她在街上走过我身旁时向我点了点头。 2. He nodded in agreement with me. 他点头表示同意我的意见。 3. The student began to nod off during math class. 那学生上数学课的时候开始打盹。 4. Trees nod in the wind. 树在风中摇曳。 5. She greeted us with a nod of the head. 她向我们点点头打招呼。', '名词: nodder 过去式: nodded 过去分词: nodded 现在分词: nodding 第三人称单数: nods');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lead', '[liːd]', 'v.引导；领先；带领；过 ... (的生活)；导致 n.领头位置；主角；榜样；引言；铅', '1. She led the way downstairs for us. 她引着我们下楼。 2. Our football team leads them by two goals. 我们的足球队比他们领先两分。 3. It\'s up to you to lead us through the difficulties. 就靠你来带领我们度过难关了。 4. They lead a busy and colourful life on the campus. 他们在大学里过着忙碌而又丰富多彩的生活。 5. She always takes the lead when we plan to do something. 我们不管打算做什么事的时候总由她来领头。', '过去式: led 过去分词: led 现在分词: leading 第三人称单数: leads');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('axis', '[\'æksɪs]', 'n.轴；中枢', '1. The earth turns (ie rotates) on its axis once every 24 hours. 地球每24小时自转一圈。 2. A wheel revolves round/on its axis. 轮子是绕轴旋转的。 3. The earth\'s axis is the line between the North and South Poles. 地轴是南北极之间的线。 4. The axis of a circle is its diameter. 圆的轴线是其直径。', '名词复数: axes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tick', '[tɪk]', 'v.滴答作响；给…标记号；运作；空转 n.滴答声；一会儿；勾号；壁虱；蜱虫；枕套；褥套；<英口>赊欠', '1. The clock ticks very loudly. 这只钟发出很响的滴答声。 2. My watch doesn\'t tick because it\'s electronic. 我的表不滴答作响,因为它是电子表。 3. The teacher ticks off a name on a list. 老师在名单上的一个名字旁打勾。 4. Listen carefully and tick the sentences which are correct. 认真听，并标记正确的句子。 5. They could hear the regular tick of the clock. 他们能听见时钟有规律的滴答声。', '过去式: ticked 过去分词: ticked 现在分词: ticking 第三人称单数: ticks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attach', '[ə\'tætʃ]', 'v.附上；系上；贴上；使依附；使附属；使附着', '1. I attach a copy of my notes for your information. 我附上笔记一份供你参考。 2. In confirmation hereof we attach a bank statement. 为作这方面的确认我们附上银行结单。 3. Please attach these labels to your hand luggages. 请把这些标签系在您的手提行李上。 4. Please attach your business card below or fill up the information. 推荐人请在下面框中贴上您的名片,如不贴名片,则请详细填写框中各项。', '形容词: attachable 名词: attachment 过去式: attached 过去分词: attached 现在分词: attaching 第三人称单数: attaches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('practitioner', '[præk\'tɪʃənər]', 'n.从业者；实践者', '1. He is an unqualified practitioner of law. 他是个无资格的律师。 2. A batch of moneybags will appear again in practitioner of domestic network game. 国内网络游戏从业者中又将出现一批富翁。 3. Socrates was the greatest practitioner of this analytical search for fundamental assumptions. 苏格拉底是这种以理性分析法探求基本假设的最伟大的实践者。 4. In Qing Dynasty Government, Li Hongzhang is the main leader and practitioner of the construction of coast defense. 李鸿章是清政府海防建设的主要领导人和实践者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('initiate', '[ɪ\'nɪʃieɪt]', 'vt.开始；创始；启蒙；介绍加入 n.创始人 adj.新加入的；启蒙的', '1. This term we will initiate a new teaching plan. 这学期我们将开始实行一个新的教学计划。 2. The company initiated a management training program for small businesses. 该公司发起了针对小企业的管理培训方案。 3. I shall initiate you into our business methods. 我将把我们的营业方法介绍给你。 4. My father wanted to initiate me into fishing. 我爸爸想教我钓鱼。', '名词: initiator 过去式: initiated 过去分词: initiated 现在分词: initiating 第三人称单数: initiates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('super', '[\'suːpər]', 'adj.超级的；极好的', '1. Now that\'s absolutely super! 这简直好极了。 2. I bought some pomegranates in the super market. 我在超市上买了一些石榴。 3. I\'ve discovered a super restaurant near here! 我在附近找到一家一流的餐馆！ 4. I\'ll be a super secretary for you. 我将成为你极好的秘书。', '过去式: supered 过去分词: supered 现在分词: supering 第三人称单数: supers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('point', '[pɔɪnt]', 'n.观点；看法；要点；重点；特点；点；地点；小数点；尖端；岬角；海角；意义；目标；分数；(罗盘上的)方位点；(温度的)点；插座；(字体)磅值 v.指；指向；朝向；瞄准；灰泥或水泥勾（某物）的砖缝', '1. I have tried to get my point across. 我已尽力让我的观点清晰明了。 2. OK, you\'ve made your point! 好了，你已经把话说清楚了。 3. I don\'t see the point of her last remark. 我不明白她最后那句话的意思。 4. He missed the whole point of my speech. 他完全没抓住我演讲的重点。 5. He pointed at the diagram to illustrate his point. 他指着图表来说明他的论点。', '过去式: pointed 过去分词: pointed 现在分词: pointing 第三人称单数: points');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('selection', '[sɪ\'lekʃn]', 'n.选择；挑选；挑选出来的人或事', '1. That shop has a fine selection of cakes. 那家商店有各种精美的糕点供我们选择。 2. That store has a good selection of furniture. 那家店有很多家具可供挑选。 3. Her selection of a dress took a long time. 她挑选一件衣服花了很长时间。 4. In making the selection we passed this short piece by quite inadvertently. 在挑选时我们完全出自疏忽而漏过了这篇短文。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('paddle', '[\'pædl]', 'n.桨；划桨；明轮翼 v.划桨；戏水；抚弄', '1. The butter churn has two paddles to whip the cream. 奶油制造机有两根搅棍搅打奶油。 2. He dipped his paddle without a splash. 他把他的短桨浸没有飞溅声。 3. Each man has a paddle for an hour and then a rest. 每个人划一个小时,然后休息一下。 4. He would himself paddle me off to the ship. 他愿亲自划船把我送上大船。', '名词: paddler 过去式: paddled 过去分词: paddled 现在分词: paddling 第三人称单数: paddles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('submerge', '[səb\'mɜːrdʒ]', 'vt.使浸没；潜入水中；覆盖 vi.浸没', '1. I watched the submarine submerge. 我望着潜艇潜入水中。', '名词: submergence 过去式: submerged 过去分词: submerged 现在分词: submerging 第三人称单数: submerges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dove', '[dʌv]', 'n.鸽子；温和派人物；鸽派人物 dive的过去式.', '1. The dove is the symbol of peace. 鸽子是和平的象征。 2. This dove was resident with us all the year round. 这只鸽子一年到头居住在这里和我们为伴。 3. Paul seemed more impressed by the dove. 保尔似乎对鸽子更感兴趣。 4. Bill was called a dove when he protested rather than fought in the war. 比尔用抗议来代替武力,因此被称为温和派。 5. She dove straight into the pool. 她径直跳入池中。', '形容词: dovish 名词: dovishness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('futile', '[\'fjuːtl]', 'adj.无效的；无用的', '1. Pace considers attempts at timing futile. 贝斯认为企图控制时间是无效的。 2. We are the Borg, Earth assimilation is inevitable, Resistant is futile! 我们是博格，地球将被同化，抵抗是无效的！ 3. It is futile to attempt to convince him that certain things are simply undoable. 使他相信某事情是完全不可为的是无用的尝试。 4. Any unrealistic objective is not worth pursuing sedulously since it is doomed to a futile project. 任何不现实的目标不值得去辛苦地追求因为它注定是无用的计划。', '副词: futilely 名词: futileness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('technique', '[tek\'niːk]', 'n.技术；技巧；技能', '1. The technique is still at the experimental stage. 这项技术正处于实验阶段。 2. The workers are trying to apply modern techniques to this traditional craft. 工人们试图将现代技术用于这项传统工业。 3. In many sports physical fitness is not as important as technique. 在许多体育运动中，体能没有技巧重要。 4. Could you project a new marketing technique for us? 你能否为我们策划一个新的市场营销技巧?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('aviation', '[ˌeɪvi\'eɪʃn]', 'n.航空；飞机制造业', '1. He devoted all his life to China\'s aviation. 他的一生都奉献给了中国的航空事业。 2. At that time aviation was still in its infancy. 当时航空仍在萌芽阶段。 3. Jets are a new development in aviation. 喷气式飞机是航空事业上的一个新成就。 4. In old China,there was hardly any machine- building industry,to say nothing of automobile and aviation industries. 旧中国几乎没有机器制造业，更不用说汽车制造业和飞机制造业了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evolve', '[i\'vɑːlv]', 'v.(使)逐步形成；(使)逐步演变；进化', '1. The American constitution was planned; the British constitution evolved. 美国宪法是精心制定的，英国宪法是约定俗成的。 2. He has evolved a new theory after many years of research. 他经过多年的研究，逐渐总结出了新的理论。 3. If women do not evolve, men definitely will change. 女人一成不变，男人一定会变。 4. Why did humans evolve to walk upright? 人类为何进化到了直立行走的姿态?', '形容词: evolvable 名词: evolvement 过去式: evolved 过去分词: evolved 现在分词: evolving 第三人称单数: evolves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('considerable', '[kən\'sɪdərəbl]', 'adj.重要的；相当大的；可观的', '1. The mayor is a considerable official. 市长是一位重要的官员。 2. He is a considerable person in that college. 他是那所学院相当重要的人物。 3. The economy was a considerable issue in the campaign. 在竞选运动中经济是一个重要问题。 4. His remarks provoked considerable comment. 他的话引起了相当大的议论。', '副词: considerably');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('criminal', '[\'krɪmɪnl]', 'n.罪犯 adj.犯罪的；刑事的；违法的', '1. The criminal was sentenced to prison for theft. 那个犯人因偷窃被判入狱。 2. Murder and stealing are criminal acts. 谋杀和偷盗都是犯罪行为。 3. I have no criminal record in my whole life. 我一生无犯罪纪录。 4. They were reinvestigating a criminal case. 他们正在复查一桩刑事案件。', '副词: criminally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('they', '[ðeɪ]', 'pron.他们', '1. Women used to think they were on the shelf at 30. 过去女人一到30岁就认为是过了结婚年龄。 2. They are going to move to a new house next week. 下星期他们将迁入新居。 3. I have a dog and a cat, but they fight all the time. 我养了一只猫和一只狗，但它们老是打架。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('opposite', '[\'ɑːpəzət]', 'adj.相反的；对面的；对立的 prep.在 ... 对面；演对手戏 adv.在对面地；处于相反位置地 n.对立物；对立者；对手', '1. She hurried away in the opposite direction. 她朝着相反的方向匆匆离去了。 2. The fireplace flamed the opposite wall. 炉火照亮了对面的墙壁。 3. Our points of view are at opposite poles. 我们的观点截然相反。 4. He came in and took a seat opposite to me. 他走进来，坐在我对面的座位上。 5. They sat opposite at the table. 他们面对面地坐在桌子两旁 6. Vice and virtue are opposites. 善和恶是对立面。', '副词: oppositely 名词: oppositeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('honey', '[\'hʌni]', 'n.蜂蜜；甜蜜；宝贝 v.说甜言蜜语；（加蜜）使甜 adj.甜蜜的；亲爱的', '1. This jar of pure honey weighs 350 grams net. 这瓶纯蜂蜜净重三百五十克。 2. We can use honey as a substitute of sugar. 我们可以蜂蜜作为糖的代替品。 3. Love is a mixture of honey and bitterness. 爱情混杂着甜蜜和苦涩。 4. Clear all these toys away before bedtime, honey. 宝贝儿，睡觉前把这些玩具都放回去。 5. He always honeyed his boss. 他总是恭维他的老板。 6. I am sorry...honey, they do not have one either. 对不起，亲爱的，他们也没有菜单。', '名词复数: honeys 过去式: honeyed/honied 过去分词: honeyed/honied 现在分词: honeying 第三人称单数: honeys');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shortly', '[\'ʃɔːrtli]', 'adv.立刻；马上', '1. Know that these aches and pains are just blockages and that they will be moved shortly. 了解这些伤痛不过只是沮滞并且将立刻被移除。 2. And it\'s hardly a coincidence that shortly after Usmanov hires a big shot PR firm these kinds of pieces begin to appear in the papers. 当乌斯马诺夫刚刚雇用了强悍的公关公司后，这类东西就立刻出现在报纸上，很难让人信服这只是一种巧合。 3. I hope to announce the winner shortly. 我希望马上宣布胜利者的名字。 4. I shall therefore be going to the bank shortly to complete these formalities so that there is no further delay in releasing the documents and consignment. 我因此将打算马上去银行来完成这些手续以便在让渡货物和文件的过程中别再耽误了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('irrigate', '[\'ɪrɪɡeɪt]', 'vi.进行灌溉 vt.灌溉；[医]冲洗', '1. They are irrigating with water. 他们正用水灌溉土地。 2. We have irrigated the desert area to make it fertile. 我们已经灌溉了荒芜地区使它肥沃。 3. They have built canals to irrigate the desert. 他们建造成水渠以灌溉沙漠。 4. They irrigate their crops with water from this river. 他们引这条河里的水灌溉庄稼。', '形容词: irrigational 名词: irrigation 过去式: irrigated 过去分词: irrigated 现在分词: irrigating 第三人称单数: irrigates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fork', '[fɔːrk]', 'n.叉；叉状物 vi.分叉 vt.使成叉形；用叉叉起', '1. He stabbed the meat with his fork/stabbed his fork into the meat. 他用叉子叉肉。 2. We came to a fork in the road and could not decide which fork we should take. 我们来到了岔路口，不能决定走哪一条岔路。 3. We parted at the fork of a road. 我们在叉路口分手。 4. The river forks here. 河流从这里分流 5. You should fork over the garden before you plant the peas. 在播种豌豆之前，你得耙耙地。', '名词: forker 过去式: forked 过去分词: forked 现在分词: forking 第三人称单数: forks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intrude', '[ɪn\'truːd]', 'v.闯入；侵入；打扰；干涉', '1. The angry visitor tried to intrude himself into the council meeting. 愤怒的来访者试图闯入会场。 2. He had no wish to intrude on their privacy. 他原本就不想触犯他们私人活动的自由。 3. A translator shouldn\'t intrude his own opinions into what he\'s translating. 译者不应该擅自把自己的意思加进译文中。 4. I don\'t want to intrude on you if you are very busy. 如果你很忙的话，我就不打扰了。', '名词: intruder 过去式: intruded 过去分词: intruded 现在分词: intruding 第三人称单数: intrudes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attractive', '[ə\'træktɪv]', 'adj.有吸引力的；有魅力的', '1. Ice-cream is attractive to children. 冰淇淋对孩子们非常有吸引力。 2. It\'s an attractive idea. 这是个使人感兴趣的想法。 3. It\'s a very attractive offer, and I\'m tempted to accept. 这项建议很有吸引力,我确实有些动心。 4. I think she is a very attractive girl. 我认为她是很有魅力的女孩。', '副词: attractively 名词: attractiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('research', '[rɪ\'sɜːrtʃ]', 'n.研究；调查 v.研究；调查', '1. We all support his scientific research. 我们都支持他的科学研究。 2. Research indicates that men find it easier to give up smoking than women. 研究表明，男人比女人更容易戒烟。 3. My research is just bouncing along at present. 目前我的调查进展得很顺利。 4. They have been researching the effects of the drug on mice. 他们一直在研究老鼠对这种药物的反应。', '形容词: researchable 名词: researcher 过去式: researched 过去分词: researched 现在分词: researching 第三人称单数: researches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plain', '[pleɪn]', 'adj.清楚的；简单的；坦白的；平常的；朴素的；纯的 n.平原；广阔的区域 adv.完全地；纯粹地', '1. It was plain to everyone that she was not happy. 她并不幸福,这是明摆着的事实。 2. The restaurant serves plain home-made meals. 那个餐馆供应简单的家常菜。 3. She was admired for her plain speaking. 她说话坦白,这一点令人钦佩。 4. Most people see great men as wizards; however, they are just plain people. 大多数人觉得伟人是奇才,然而,他们只不过是平常人。 5. The wind whipped across the plain. 大风扫过平原。 6. Beck went plain crazy with anger on the day when he received his Dear John from his girlfriend. 贝克收到他女朋友的绝交信的那天简直都气疯了。', '副词: plainly 比较级: plainer 最高级: plainest 名词: plainness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weekday', '[\'wiːkdeɪ]', 'n.工作日', '1. I don\'t stay out late on weekdays. 工作日的时候我不在外面呆得很晚。 2. The library is open on weekdays only. 这个图书馆星期一至星期六都开放。 3. You can have your goods delivered on any weekday. 您要求在任何工作日装运货物均可。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cent', '[sent]', 'n.分', '1. I\'m a hundred per cent certain. 我百分之百地肯定。 2. I don\'t have a cent with me. 我身上一分钱也没有。 3. The coins of the lowest denomination is the cent. 钱币的最低单位是分。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hill', '[hɪl]', 'n.小山；丘陵；山冈；斜坡 vt.堆起；培土', '1. Trees crowned the hill. 树木覆盖着小山。 2. We found the animal on a scrub hill. 我们在一个灌木丛生的丘陵上找到这动物。 3. The hill was buried under 11 inches of snow. 这丘陵上覆盖着11英寸厚的大雪。 4. We walked down the hill before sunset. 我们在日落前走下山冈。 5. Would you please hill the leaves in the backyard? 你能把后院的树叶扫成堆吗?', '名词: hiller 过去式: hilled 过去分词: hilled 现在分词: hilling 第三人称单数: hills');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('handy', '[\'hændi]', 'adj.方便的；手边的；灵巧的；近便的；现成的', '1. An electric kettle is very handy. 电水壶使用非常方便。 2. The sailors clung to anything handy. 水手们紧紧抓住手边任何东西。 3. He is very handy at repairing clocks. 他修钟表很灵巧。 4. It is quite a handy little sailing boat. 这是一个相当灵巧的小帆船。', '比较级: handier 最高级: handiest 名词: handiness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grateful', '[\'ɡreɪtfl]', 'adj.感激的；令人愉快的', '1. I can\'t express how grateful I am. 我说不出我有多么感激。 2. These refugees are very grateful to the government\'s succor. 这些难民非常感激政府的救援。 3. I am grateful for all your past kindness. 多蒙关照,万分感激。 4. I\'d be grateful if you should let me know as soon as possible. 你若能让我尽快知道,我会很感激的。', '副词: gratefully 名词: gratefulness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reservoir', '[\'rezərvwɑːr]', 'n.水库；储藏；蓄水池；积蓄', '1. Fresh water was at a premium after the reservoir was contaminated. 在水库被污染之后,清水便因稀而贵了。 2. They open the sluice gates of reservoir. 他们打开水库的闸门。 3. His mind is a reservoir of facts. 他的心是事实的储藏处。 4. To begin to understand why, remember that water in a reservoir naturally flows preferentially to any crack in the dam. 要探究原因，可以联想一下蓄水池的水，当水坝有裂缝时，水很自然的会先由裂缝流出。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('howl', '[haʊl]', 'n.长嚎；高声叫喊；啸鸣 v.嚎叫；大声哭；吼叫着说出', '1. The howl seemed to freeze the world with fear. 那嚎叫声好像要令整个世界毛骨悚然。 2. You can grip the club when you hear the wolf howl. 听见狼嚎你可以握紧棍子。 3. A sudden howl pierced the silence. 突然一声嗥叫划破了寂静。 4. They listened to the howl of the wind through the trees. 他们听着风在林间呼啸的声音。 5. The dog howled over its master\'s body. 狗对着主人的尸体哀嚎。', '过去式: howled 过去分词: howled 现在分词: howling 第三人称单数: howls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('confidential', '[ˌkɑːnfɪ\'denʃl]', 'adj.秘密的；机密的；表示信任的；获信赖的', '1. He has been on confidential missions to Berlin. 他前往柏林执行秘密任务。 2. He told me the confidential information. 他向我透露了这个秘密的信息。 3. He was an author whose works were so little known as to be almost confidential. 他这位作家的著作是如此不为人所知，以致几乎等于机密文件。 4. Don\'t be too confidential with strangers. 不要过份相信陌生人。', '副词: confidentially 名词: confidentiality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('already', '[ɔːl\'redi]', 'adv.已经', '1. I\'ve already paid my membership dues. 我已经交了我的会员费。 2. The new rules have already come into play. 新规则已经开始生效。 3. You had already gone when I arrived there. 当我到达时，你已经走了。 4. I\'ve been there already and don\'t want to go again. 我曾到过那，不想再去了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assess', '[ə\'ses]', 'v.评定；评估；估算', '1. He can quickly assess a person\'s character. 他能很快地评定出某人的品质。 2. How do you assess your students? 你如何评估学生们？ 3. We will assess the damages caused by the flood. 我们将对洪灾造成的损失进行评估。 4. She looked at the house and assessed its market value. 她看了看房子并估算了其市场价值。', '形容词: assessable 过去式: assessed 过去分词: assessed 现在分词: assessing 第三人称单数: assesses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('empirical', '[ɪm\'pɪrɪkl]', 'adj.经验主义的；以观察或实验为根据的', '1. His science was generally empirical and often bad. 他的科学一般来自经验。 2. Inquiry into the nature of things based on logical reasoning rather than empirical methods. 自然科学基于逻辑推理而不是凭经验得来的方法来探究事物的本质。 3. Unboundedness has a greater empirical credibility. 无界性有更大的经验可信性。 4. The Sprint phase is an empirical process. 冲刺阶段是一个完全根据经验的过程。', '副词: empirically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('charter', '[\'tʃɑːrtər]', 'n.宪章；特许；(船、机、车等的)租赁 vt.包租；特许；发给 ... 执照 adj.特许的', '1. You should read the Charter of the United Nations. 你应该阅读一下联合国宪章。 2. The rights of our citizens are governed by charter. 我们公民的权利是由宪章规定的。 3. The company was granted a charter trade in the occupied territory. 这家公司被授予特权，可以在被占领地区进行贸易活动。 4. The holiday-makers chartered a boat to go fishing. 渡假者租了一艘船去钓鱼。', '名词: charterer 过去式: chartered 过去分词: chartered 现在分词: chartering 第三人称单数: charters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('paralyze', '[\'pærəˌlaɪz]', 'vt. 使 ... 瘫痪； 使目瞪口呆 =paralyse（英）', '1. Otherwise, my dread of criticism can paralyze me. 不然的话，我对批评的恐惧将让我行为瘫痪。 2. Even the smallest slip could permanently paralyze the patient. 即使最小的失误都会导致小朱利安终身瘫痪。', '副词: paralyzingly 名词: paralyzation 过去式: paralyzed 过去分词: paralyzed 现在分词: paralyzing 第三人称单数: paralyzes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('power', '[\'paʊər]', 'n.力量；力；能力；权力；【数】幂；电力 v.使有力量；给 ... 提供动力 adj.电力的；力量的；权力的', '1. A man should rely upon his own power. 人类应该依靠自身的力量。 2. Such things aren\'t within the compass of my power. 这些事不在我力可能及的范围之内。 3. I intend to release my karma to give power away. 我意愿释放我送给别人力量的业力。 4. Not that I don\'t want to help you, but that it\'s beyond my power to do so. 并不是我不想帮忙,而是我能力有限。 5. So you need to power up your lymph system. 因此你需要增强淋巴系统的功能。 6. She\'s gone to some power lunch to discuss the deal. 她赴巨头午餐会商讨此事。', '过去式: powered 过去分词: powered 现在分词: powering 第三人称单数: powers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crisp', '[krɪsp]', 'adj.脆的；干脆的；卷曲的；明快的；(天气)干冷的 n.薯片；松脆物 v.(使)发脆；(使)卷曲', '1. It tastes sweet and crisp. 吃起来又甜又脆。 2. I like the delicious salad of crisp lettuce and tomatos. 我喜欢这种脆莴苣和番茄做的沙拉，很好吃。 3. Her voice was crisp and authoritative. 她的声音干脆利落，具有权威性。 4. You see how the finish is much more crisp than the rest of the hair. 大家看到了,成型的头发比其余的头发看起来更卷曲。 5. I lay in the sun all day and got burnt to a crisp. 我在太阳下躺了一整天，都快烤焦了。 6. These biscuits have gone soft,you\'d better crisp them up in the oven. 这些饼干变软了，你最好把它们放在烘炉上烤脆。', '副词: crisply 比较级: crisper 最高级: crispest 名词: crispness 过去式: crisped 过去分词: crisped 现在分词: crisping 第三人称单数: crisps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('knee', '[niː]', 'n.膝盖；膝关节', '1. I\'ve bumped my knee on the wall. 我的膝盖撞上了墙壁。 2. I bounced the baby on my knee. 我把婴儿放在膝上上下颠着。 3. His left knee was hurt in a traffic accident. 他的左膝在一次交通事故中受伤了。', '过去式: kneed 过去分词: kneed 现在分词: kneeing 第三人称单数: knees');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('below', '[bɪ\'loʊ]', 'prep.低于；在 ... 下面 adv.在下面；向下', '1. His income is well below the average. 他的收入大大低于平均水平。 2. The class has dropped below ten students this year. 今年这个班的学生降到了10人以下。 3. Please do not write below this line. 请不要写到这条线下面。 4. The information below was compiled by our correspondent. 以下资料是我们的记者收集整理的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dedicate', '[\'dedɪkeɪt]', 'vt.致力于；献出；提献辞', '1. She dedicated her life to science. 她毕生致力于科学。 2. I will dedicate myself to science in the future. 我将来一定要投身于科学事业。 3. I dedicate this song to my wife. 我要把这首歌献给我太太。 4. I\'d like to dedicate the book to my parents. 我想把这本书献给我的父母。', '名词: dedicator 过去式: dedicated 过去分词: dedicated 现在分词: dedicating 第三人称单数: dedicates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('route', '[ruːt]', 'n.路线；(固定)线路；途径 vt.为 ... 安排路线；(按路线)发送', '1. The route was once much travelled but has fallen into disuse. 这条路线旅行的人以前常走，但是现在已不用了。 2. The bus route goes so far as that, so you\'ll need to take a taxi. 汽车路线到此为止了，你得叫辆的士。 3. The plane deviated from its usual route. 飞机偏离了正常的航线。 4. Professor Layard argues that higher income is a route to higher status. 莱亚德教授提出,增加收入是提高地位的一个途径。 5. The flight is routed to Chicago via New York. 这个航班被安排经纽约飞往芝加哥。', '过去式: routed 过去分词: routed 现在分词: routing 第三人称单数: routes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bang', '[bæŋ]', 'n.巨响；重击；刘海 v.重击；大声敲；剪成刘海；突然巨响 adv.正好地；准确地', '1. The door shut with a bang. 门砰的一声关上了。 2. He was awakened by a terrific bang. 一声巨响把他从睡梦中惊醒。 3. He fell and got a nasty bang on the head. 他跌了一跤，头部磕得很重。 4. She is keeping a long bang. 她现在是留着长刘海。 5. He fell and banged his knee. 他跌倒了，膝盖重重撞了一下。 6. The light went out bang in the middle of the performance. 表演正好进行到一半时停电了。', '过去式: banged 过去分词: banged 现在分词: banging 第三人称单数: bangs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tent', '[tent]', 'n.帐篷 v.住帐篷；宿营', '1. They set up a tent near the seashore. 他们在海滨附近搭起了一个帐篷。 2. The wind caused the tent to collapse. 风把帐篷吹塌了。 3. Please slacken the tent rope before it rains. 下雨前，请将帐篷的绳索放松。 4. The tent flaps should be tightly fastened. 帐篷的帘布应紧紧系住。 5. Last night, we tented in the forest. 昨夜我们在森林里住帐篷。', '过去式: tented 过去分词: tented 现在分词: tenting 第三人称单数: tents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deceive', '[dɪ\'siːv]', 'vt.欺骗 vi.行骗', '1. It\'s not honorable to deceive them. 欺骗他们是不光彩的。 2. He was foiled in his attempt to deceive us. 他企图欺骗我们,但没有得逞。 3. He deceived me into signing the papers. 他骗我在文件上签了字。 4. You are deceiving yourself if you still believe that she loves you. 你如果还相信她爱你，你就是在欺骗自己。 5. Appearances can deceive. 外表是有欺骗性的。', '形容词: deceivable 副词: deceivingly 名词: deceiver 过去式: deceived 过去分词: deceived 现在分词: deceiving 第三人称单数: deceives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diet', '[\'daɪət]', 'n.日常食物；规定饮食；节食 n.（日本等国的）国会 v.节食；照规定饮食；喂食', '1. Too rich a diet (ie Too much rich food) is not good for you. 吃太多油腻的食物对你身体不好。 2. You should eat more high-protein diet. 你应该多吃些高蛋白食物。 3. Her diet restricts her to 1500 calories a day. 她的规定饮食限制她每天摄入1500卡的热量。 4. The doctor says I\'ve got to go on a diet. 医生说我得节食。 5. The Diet will have a long session. 国会将有长会期。 6. You ought to diet and take more exercise. 你应该节食并多做运动。', '名词: dieter 过去式: dieted 过去分词: dieted 现在分词: dieting 第三人称单数: diets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('worker', '[\'wɜːrkər]', 'n.工人；工作者', '1. The worker\'s overalls were badly burned by acid. 这位工人的工作装被酸腐蚀得很厉害。 2. The boss dispenses the sick worker from his duties. 老板准许生病的工人不上班。 3. She has been held up as a model worker. 她被推举为模范工作者。 4. A health worker immunizes an infant in Nepal. 医疗工作者在尼泊尔为婴儿注射预防针。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('glue', '[ɡluː]', 'n.胶；胶水；胶粘物 vt.粘贴；紧附于', '1. This extra strong glue should do the job nicely. 这种超强度胶应该管用。 2. This glue doesn\'t stick very well. 这种胶水粘不住。 3. The poster wouldn\'t stick even though I drenched it with glue. 我涂了大量胶水，可那张海报就是贴不住。 4. He glued a stamp onto the envelope. 他把邮票贴在信封上。', '形容词: gluey 名词: gluiness 过去式: glued 过去分词: glued 现在分词: gluing 第三人称单数: glues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('officer', '[\'ɔːfɪsər]', 'n.官员；高级职员；警官；军官；办事员', '1. That officer must be removed. 那位官员必须免职。 2. He doubts if the officer is anybody. 他怀疑这官员是个要人。 3. The immigration officer stamped my passport. 移民官员在我的护照上盖了戳。 4. His father was a senior officer at the bank. 他父亲是那家银行的高级职员。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fuel', '[\'fjuːəl]', 'n.燃料；刺激因素 vt.供以燃料 vi.加燃料', '1. Coal is used as fuel. 煤用作燃料。 2. We aim for a 10% saving in fuel. 我们的目标是节省10%的燃料。 3. His indifference was a fuel to her hatred. 他无动于衷使她心中的怨恨火上加油。 4. Higher salaries helped to fuel inflation. 工资提高刺激通货膨胀。 5. All aircraft must fuel before flight. 所有飞机飞行前都必须加油。', '名词: fueler 过去式: fueled/fuelled 过去分词: fueled/fuelled 现在分词: fueling/fuelling 第三人称单数: fuels/fuels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('label', '[\'leɪbl]', 'n.标记；标签；称号；唱片公司 vt.贴标签于；把 ... 归类', '1. Put a label on your luggage. 在你行李上做个标记。 2. I read the information on the label before deciding which jam to buy. 我先看果酱标签上的说明再决定买哪种. 3. He has been given a label of \"playboy\" by his friends. 他的朋友给他起了一个“花花公子”的绰号。 4. It\'s his first release for a major label. 这是他在大唱片公司发行的第一张唱片。 5. The bottle is labeled poison. 瓶上标明有毒。', '名词: labeler 过去式: labeled/labelled 过去分词: labeled/labelled 现在分词: labeling/labelling 第三人称单数: labels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spell', '[spel]', 'v.拼写；拼成；导致；暂时代替 n.咒语；魔力；一段时间；一阵发作；轮班', '1. I don\'t know how to spell your name. 我不会拼写你的名字。 2. Can you spell the word\" metropolis\"? 你会拼写“metropolis”这个词吗? 3. Her writing is neat, but she can\'t spell. 她的书写很工整，但是她不会拼写。 4. Put them all together, and they spell MOTHER. 把它们拼在一起 5. The witch put the princess under a spell, and she fell asleep for ten years. 这女巫使公主中了巫术，沉睡了十年。', '过去式: spelled/spelt 过去分词: spelled/spelt 现在分词: spelling 第三人称单数: spells');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('breath', '[breθ]', 'n.呼吸；气息', '1. He caught his breath in surprise. 他惊奇得屏住了呼吸。 2. His chest heaves with every breath. 他的胸部随着呼吸而起伏。 3. It took us a few minutes to get our breath back after the race. 赛跑后我们用了好几分钟才恢复了正常呼吸。 4. His breath smelt suspiciously of drink. 他嘴里呼出的气息好象有酒味。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('missing', '[\'mɪsɪŋ]', 'adj.失踪的；失去的；漏掉的 动词miss的现在分词形式.', '1. Police are combing the woods for the missing children. 警察搜遍树林以寻找失踪的孩子。 2. With a bit of luck she\'ll find her missing ring. 但愿她有幸找到她丢失的戒指。 3. I will print in the missing manes for you. 我会帮你把漏掉的名字加进去的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skyscraper', '[\'skaɪskreɪpər]', 'n.摩天大楼', '1. A new skyscraper has been put up downtown. 市中心又建起了一座摩天大厦。 2. The skyscraper towers into the sky. 该摩天大楼高耸入云。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blast', '[blæst]', 'n.爆炸；巨响；一阵(强风)；严厉的批评；<美俚>愉快的经历 v.爆破；摧毁；发出巨响；用力撞击；批评', '1. 27 school children were injured in the blast. 27名学龄儿童在爆炸中受了伤。 2. A blast of the trumpet gave her a start. 突然发出的喇叭声吓了她一跳。 3. A blast of wind blew my hat off. 一阵风吹走了我的帽子。 4. The press responded to his remarks with a blast of criticism. 新闻界以严厉的批评回应了他的言论。 5. A massive car bomb blasted the police headquarters. 一个巨大的汽车炸弹在警局总部爆炸。', '名词: blaster 过去式: blasted 过去分词: blasted 现在分词: blasting 第三人称单数: blasts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adjoin', '[ə\'dʒɔɪn]', 'v.邻接；毗连', '1. We heard laughter in the adjoining room. 我们听到了邻屋的笑声。 2. The playing field adjoins the school. 体育场紧靠着学校。 3. Our house adjoins theirs. 我们的房屋与他们的毗连。', '过去式: adjoined 过去分词: adjoined 现在分词: adjoining 第三人称单数: adjoins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('miserable', '[\'mɪzrəbl]', 'adj.痛苦的；悲惨的；贫乏的；狼狈的', '1. Her wretchedness made him feel miserable. 她的不幸让他感到十分难受。 2. You made Grace Howland\'s life miserable. 你使格雷斯·豪兰的生活痛苦不堪。 3. The handmaid led a miserable life. 婢女过着悲惨的生活。 4. There are still many people whose living conditions are miserable. 仍有许多人的生活条件是很艰苦的。', '副词: miserably 名词: miserableness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overseas', '[ˌoʊvər\'siːz]', 'adj.海外的 adv.在海外', '1. The overseas trade has become the main project. 海外贸易成为主要的项目。 2. She is an overseas student in Britain. 她是个在英国的外国留学生。 3. Over the years, hundreds of overseas students have studied at that university. 几年来，几百个留学生在那所大学学习过。 4. He lived overseas for many years. 他在海外生活了多年。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('denial', '[dɪ\'naɪəl]', 'n.否认；拒绝', '1. The accusation brought a speedy denial. 指责马上遭到否认。 2. The prisoner repeated denials of the charges against him. 囚犯对被控罪名再三否认。 3. He met the charge with a plump denial. 他断然否认对他的指控。 4. The government has issued a denial of an election in May. 政府发表声明否认五月份要进行选举。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('when', '[wen]', 'adv.什么时候；当 ... 时 conj.然后；可是；当 ... 时 pron.什么时候 n.时间', '1. When did that happen? 那件事是什么时候发生的？ 2. They stood respectfully when he entered the room. 当他走进房间时，他们都恭恭敬敬地站着。 3. Iron will melt when it is made very hot. 当铁烧得很热时就会熔化的。 4. And they roared when Seaman held up two fingers. 然后当希曼伸出两根指头的时候他们就吼叫起来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clutch', '[klʌtʃ]', 'vt.抓住；抓牢 vi.企图抓住；踩离合器 n.抓住；爪子；离合器；紧要关头 n.一窝鸡（蛋）；一群 adj.关键的；致胜的', '1. The boy clutched the marbles and ran away. 那男孩一把抢去弹珠便逃之夭夭。 2. The child clutched his toy. 那个孩子紧抓着他的玩具不放。 3. John jumped up to clutch at the branch,but missed. 约翰跳起来试图抓住那树枝，但是没有成功。 4. It is useless to clutch at a straw. 抓救命稻草是无济于事的。 5. The eagle flew away with a rabbit in the clutch of its claws. 鹰用爪子紧紧抓住一只野兔，飞走了。 6. He\'s won a whole clutch of awards. 他获得一大堆奖。 7. Tmac is a choker and will never be able to get it done during clutch time. 麦迪就像一条围巾，在关键的时候很难从脖子上取下来。', '过去式: clutched 过去分词: clutched 现在分词: clutching 第三人称单数: clutches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('educate', '[\'edʒukeɪt]', 'v.教育；培养；训练', '1. It is not easy to educate teenagers. 教育青少年不是件容易的事。 2. An educator must first educate himself. 教育者必须自己先受教育。 3. He tried to educate his wife\'s taste in literature. 他试图培养他太太对文学的爱好。 4. Senator Fulbright also believed the program could educate future world leaders. 富布莱特参议员也相信，这个基金方案能培养出未来的世界领袖。', '过去式: educated 过去分词: educated 现在分词: educating 第三人称单数: educates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('carve', '[kɑːrv]', 'v.雕刻；切割', '1. The statue was carved out of marble. 这座雕像是用大理石雕刻的。 2. We will look for a pumpkin, to carve into a jack-o-lantern. 我们将要找一颗南瓜来雕刻成南瓜灯。 3. He carved me some very nice pieces of chicken. 他为我切了几块很好的鸡肉。 4. It\'s your turn to carve the meat. 该你来把肉切开了。', '名词: carver 过去式: carved 过去分词: carved 现在分词: carving 第三人称单数: carves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sauce', '[sɔːs]', 'n.酱汁；调味汁；<口>无礼 vt.给 ... 调味；使 ... 增加趣味；对 ... 无礼', '1. Waiter, may I have steak sauce, please？ 服务生,请给我一些牛排酱汁。 2. The sauce is thin and tasteless. 这酱汁淡而无味。 3. The cook poured the sauce over the food. 厨师将调味汁倒在食物上。 4. The secret of this dish is in the sauce. 这道菜好吃的秘诀在于调味汁。 5. He sauced criticism with flattery 他用谄媚来冲淡批评。', '过去式: sauced 过去分词: sauced 现在分词: saucing 第三人称单数: sauces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('admission', '[əd\'mɪʃn]', 'n.承认；入会费；许可', '1. He is a coward by his own admission. 他自己承认是个胆小鬼。 2. He was, on his own admission, impulsive by nature. 他承认自己生性易于感情冲动。 3. Do they charge for admission? 入场要收费吗? 4. The charge for admission is US$5. 入场费五美元。', '形容词: admissive');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('carrier', '[\'kæriər]', 'n.航空母舰；运输工具；行李架；带菌者；运送者；客运公司；电信公司', '1. The missile was launched from the aircraft carrier. 导弹是从航空母舰上发射的。 2. The carrier is armed with nuclear weapons. 那艘航空母舰有核武器。 3. Airplanes were launched from the aircraft carrier. 飞机从航空母舰上起飞了。 4. We\'re discussing about the Network flow problem with carrier. 我们正在商讨带运输工具的网络流问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('border', '[\'bɔːrdər]', 'n.边界；边境；边缘 vt.与 ... 接壤；加边于 vi.近似；毗邻', '1. We have a herbaceous border round our garden. 我们的花园四周种有草本植物。 2. A series of provocations led up to the border war. 一系列的挑衅事件导致了边境战争的发生。 3. Enemy troops raided our border areas. 敌军对我边境地区进行袭击。 4. I lost a white handkerchief with a blue border. 我丢了一块带蓝色花边的白手绢。 5. France borders Germany along parts of the Rhine. 法国沿莱茵河部分河段与德国接壤。 6. Some of his statements are so incorrect that they border on fraudulence. 他的某些说法非常不正确以致近乎欺诈。', '名词: borderer 过去式: bordered 过去分词: bordered 现在分词: bordering 第三人称单数: borders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('filter', '[\'fɪltər]', 'n.过滤器；滤色镜；滤光器 v.过滤；渗透', '1. We usually clear the water with a filter. 我们通常用过滤器使水净化。 2. You can also filter to focus on specific areas. 你也可以设置过滤器来只关注一些特定的区域。 3. Filter selection is made using inherent spectra. 滤色镜的选择必须利用固有光谱。 4. A yellow filter is placed in front of the camera lens to assure that no blue light will be imaged. 为了不使蓝光进入相机而成像，可在相机的透镜前加一黄滤色镜。 5. It won\'t take long to filter the coffee. 用不了多少时间就可以把咖啡过滤好。', '形容词: filterless 名词: filterer 过去式: filtered 过去分词: filtered 现在分词: filtering 第三人称单数: filters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pope', '[poʊp]', 'n.罗马教皇', '1. The Pope retreats to Castelgondolfo every summer. 罗马教皇每年夏天都退避到圣得罗。 2. Pope John XXIII once was invited to France to attend a banquet. 有一次，罗马教皇约翰二十三世应邀出席法国的一个盛大宴会，一位着装十分暴露的女士正巧坐在他的身边。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Friday', '[\'fraɪdeɪ]', 'n.星期五', '1. They reached London on Friday. 他们星期五到达伦敦。 2. We will do a Chemistry experiment this Friday. 这个周五我们要做化学试验。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('overwhelming', '[ˌoʊvər\'welmɪŋ]', 'adj.势不可挡的；压倒的；无法抗拒的', '1. He bounced back by winning an overwhelming election victory. 他通过赢得一次势不可挡的选举胜利迅速恢复了过来。 2. The scenic splendors of the Rocky Mountains are overwhelming. 落基山脉的壮丽景色使人赞叹不已。 3. Our football team has won an overwhelming victory. 我们的足球队取得了压倒性的胜利。 4. The general effect of the painting is overwhelming. 这幅画给人总的印象是很有气势。', '副词: overwhelmingly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('electricity', '[ɪˌlek\'trɪsəti]', 'n.电；电学；电流；热情', '1. The electricity failure paralyzed the water supply. 停电使水供应陷于瘫痪。 2. The interruption of electricity made us unable to do anything. 电力的中断让我们什么也不能做。 3. While I was cooking supper the electricity went off. 我正在做晚饭时停电了。 4. Both students have made quite a few experiments on electricity. 这两个学生都做了不少电学实验。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('phase', '[feɪz]', 'n.相位；方面；局面；阶段；时期 vt.逐步执行', '1. No phase transition evidence is found. 没有发现任何相位跃迁的证据。 2. Distortion can result from phase shifts. 相位变化将造成失真。 3. This is but one phase of the subject. 这仅是问题的一个方面。 4. They are talking about the changing phases of society. 他们谈论着不断变化的社会状况。 5. The use of lead-free petrol is now being phased in. 无铅汽油的应用现正逐步推广。', '形容词: phasic 过去式: phased 过去分词: phased 现在分词: phasing 第三人称单数: phases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pronunciation', '[prəˌnʌnsi\'eɪʃn]', 'n.发音；读音', '1. His pronunciation is simply terrible. 他的发音太糟了。 2. Your faults of pronunciation can be remedied. 你的发音毛病是可以纠正的。 3. He learns pronunciation by imitating the teacher. 他是向老师模仿来学习发音的。 4. He forgot the pronunciation of this word. 他把这个字的读音忘了。', '形容词: pronunciational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bulb', '[bʌlb]', 'n.球茎；电灯泡；球状物', '1. Onions and lilies grow from bulbs. 洋葱和百合是从球茎中长出的。 2. This light bulb has gone. 这灯泡不亮了。 3. The light bulb imploded. 这灯泡是向内侧爆裂的。 4. I can see clearly that the filament in the bulb is broken. 我可以很清楚地看到灯泡里的细丝断了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tour', '[tʊr]', 'n.旅游；观光；巡回 v.周游；旅行；巡回', '1. They\'re going on a world tour. 他们正在环球旅行。 2. We are going on a tour of the city this afternoon. 我们今天下午要到城里去观光。 3. He went on a speaking tour of the United States. 他去美国作巡回演讲。 4. She plans to tour about the world. 她打算周游世界。', '名词: tourer 过去式: toured 过去分词: toured 现在分词: touring 第三人称单数: tours');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('credential', '[krə\'denʃl]', 'n.国书；凭据；印信 vt.提供证明书 adj.信任的', '1. Is the name of the credential to remove from the server. 要从服务器中删除的凭据的名称。 2. The passwords that are used to protect the master keys are stored in the credential store. 用于保护主密钥的密码存储在凭据存储区中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whichever', '[wɪtʃ\'evər]', 'adj.无论哪个；无论哪些 pron.无论哪个', '1. Whichever nation explodes an atomic bomb will engage the whole world in war. 无论哪个国家使用原子弹都会使全世界卷入战争。 2. Whichever nation explodes an atomic bomb will engage the whole world in war. 无论哪个国家使用原子弹都会使全世界卷入战争。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nut', '[nʌt]', 'n.坚果；果仁 n.螺母；螺帽；难对付的人(事) vi.采坚果', '1. He carefully cracked a nut and then give it to me. 他仔细敲开一颗坚果,然后递给了我。 2. The little boy is trying to crack the shell open to get at the nut 这个小男孩在使劲敲破外壳取得果仁。 3. When we turn the nut, we raise or lower the bob. 我们一转动螺母，就会升高或降低摆锤。 4. He soon came up with a nut which had fallen off. 一会儿他来了，拿着一颗脱落下来的螺帽。 5. The kids are nutting in the forest like squirrels. 孩子们像小松鼠一样在森林里采集坚果。', '名词: nutter 过去式: nutted 过去分词: nutted 现在分词: nutting 第三人称单数: nuts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rust', '[rʌst]', 'n.铁锈；锈菌；赤褐色 vi.生锈；变成锈色 vt.使 ... 生锈；损害', '1. The tools will corrode with rust if never used. 这些工具如长期不用会长铁锈而损坏。 2. Rust is eating away the iron hinge. 铁锈正腐蚀着铁铰链。 3. The pipes had clogged with rust. 铁锈阻塞了管道。 4. How can I remove the rust from the iron door? 我怎样才能把铁门上的锈除掉呢？ 5. Iron exposed to damp air will rust. 放在空气潮湿地方的铁会生锈。 6. The rain will rust the iron roof. 雨水将使铁皮屋顶生锈。', '形容词: rustable 过去式: rusted 过去分词: rusted 现在分词: rusting 第三人称单数: rusts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comply', '[kəm\'plaɪ]', 'vi.顺从；遵照；答应', '1. She was told to pay the fine, but refused to comply. 通知她交纳罚款，但她拒不服从。 2. He was willing to comply with my proposal. 他愿意顺从我的建议。 3. Everyone should comply with the law. 每个人都应该遵守法律。 4. Is it our duty to comply with his requests? 我们有义务满足他的要求吗?', '过去式: complied 过去分词: complied 现在分词: complying 第三人称单数: complies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('adult', '[\'ædʌlt]', 'n.成年人；成年动物 adj.成年的；理智的；适合成年人的；成熟的', '1. Child who is not accompanied by an adult will not be admitted. 儿童无成人带领不得入内。 2. The bear was a fully grown adult. 那只熊已完全发育成熟. 3. He spent his adult life in Canada. 他在加拿大度过了他的成年时期。 4. Can you try and be a little more adult about this? 你能不能试着更理智一点地看待这件事？', '名词: adulthood');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stationery', '[\'steɪʃəneri]', 'n.文具；信笺', '1. He\'s been helping himself to my stationery. 他未经许可一直用我的文具。 2. My stationery cupboard is full of paper. 我的文具柜塞满了纸。 3. The letter is typed on his office stationery. 这件信打在他办公室专用信纸上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prevent', '[prɪ\'vent]', 'v.预防；防止，阻止；挡住', '1. Scientists are trying to find ways to prevent disease. 科学家们正试图找到预防疾病的方法。 2. It is the job of the police to prevent crime. 防止犯罪是警察的职责。 3. Nothing can prevent us from carrying out the plan. 什么也无法阻挡我们去实施这个计划。 4. Ways must be found to prevent the poisonous gases from polluting the air. 一定要找到办法防止有毒气体污染空气。', '形容词: preventable 名词: preventability 过去式: prevented 过去分词: prevented 现在分词: preventing 第三人称单数: prevents');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('biscuit', '[\'bɪskɪt]', 'n.饼干；淡褐色', '1. He had some biscuits before the dinner. 晚饭前，他吃了一些饼干。 2. I caught her with her fingers in the biscuit tin. 我看见她手指还在饼干盒里呢。 3. Children like to eat the biscuit. 孩子们喜欢吃饼干。', '名词复数: biscuits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('flash', '[flæʃ]', 'v.闪光；闪现；掠过；忽然...；亵渎性暴露 n.闪光（灯）；恍然大悟；一刹那；闪现；[计算机]Adobe公司的动画技术', '1. Lighthouse and beacons flash at night. 晚上灯塔与信号灯闪着光。 2. A driver is not supposed to flash his lights at the coming vehicles. 司机不该朝着迎面开来的车辆闪灯。 3. Her eyes flashed with anger. 她眼中冒出了怒火。 4. The days seem to flash by. 光阴似箭。 5. Flashes are not allowed to be used in this museum. 这个博物馆里不准使用闪光灯。', '过去式: flashed 过去分词: flashed 现在分词: flashing 第三人称单数: flashes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('echo', '[\'ekoʊ]', 'vi.发出回声；回响 vt.重复；模仿；附和 n.回声；重复；共鸣 Echo. n.[希神]山林女神（失恋于那喀索斯；其哀声留于山间成为回声）', '1. His voice echoed in the big empty hall. 他的声音在空荡的大厅里发出回声。 2. Our songs echoed over the mountains and seas. 我们的歌声在山海之间回响。 3. The room echoed with their happy laughter. 房间里回荡着他们的欢笑声。 4. I would like to echo the words of the previous speaker. 我想重复前面一位发言者的话。 5. She shouted on the mountaintop and listened to the echo. 她在山顶上大声喊着,然后聆听着回声。', '形容词: echoey 名词: echoer 名词复数: echoes 过去式: echoed 过去分词: echoed 现在分词: echoing 第三人称单数: echoes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('must', '[mʌst]', 'aux.必须；应当；很可能 n.必须做的事；未发酵的葡萄汁；发霉', '1. Something must be done about it. 必须得想个办法。 2. In England traffic must keep to the left. 在英国，车辆必须靠左行驶。 3. We must make allowance for his youth. 我们应当考虑到他还年轻。 4. One must honor his contract and keep his word. 任何人都应当尊重合同，信守诺言。 5. A raincoat is a must in the rainy season. 在雨季雨衣是必备之物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('allow', '[ə\'laʊ]', 'vt.允许；让某人得到；留出；同意（法律） vi.(for)考虑到；允许', '1. You are not allowed to smoke here. 这里不许吸烟。 2. How much holiday are you allowed? 你有多少天假? 3. I should allow an hour to get to London. 到伦敦去我得留出一小时来。 4. The judge assented to allow the prisoner to speak. 法官同意允许犯人申辩。 5. It will take you half an hour to get to the station, allowing for traffic delays. 把路上的耽搁算进去，你要用半小时才能到车站。', '形容词: allowable 副词: allowably 过去式: allowed 过去分词: allowed 现在分词: allowing 第三人称单数: allows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mainland', '[\'meɪnlænd]', 'n.大陆；本土', '1. The programs will be beamed to Mainland China. 这些节目将对中国大陆播放。 2. The island is joined to the mainland by a bridge. 岛上有座桥与大陆相连。 3. Bombay is linked to the mainland by a causeway. 孟买和印度本土是由一条堤道相连的。 4. Hawaii and Alaska are not on the mainland of the United States. 夏威夷和阿拉斯加不在美国本土。', '名词: mainlander');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hire', '[\'haɪər]', 'v.雇用；出租 n.租金；雇用；租用', '1. We don\'t want to hire inexperienced worker. 我们不想聘用没有经验的工人。 2. We hired an advertising company for help to sell our product. 我们雇用了一家广告公司来推销我们的产品。 3. Lawyers are men who hire out their words and anger. 律师,是把自己的言辞与愤怒出租于人的人。 4. They hire out boats by the hour. 他们按小时出租小船。 5. He paid the carriage hire to the driver. 他把马车租金给了马车夫。', '形容词: hirable 名词: hirer 过去式: hired 过去分词: hired 现在分词: hiring 第三人称单数: hires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('division', '[dɪ\'vɪʒn]', 'n.划分；除法；部门；分开；师（军队）', '1. The divisions between the various classes of society are not so sharply marked as they used to be. 现在社会上各阶级的划分不象过去那样明显了。 2. The boy has learnt to do division. 这个小男孩已学会做除法。 3. He works in the foreign division of the company. 他在公司的外事部工作。 4. There was a division of opinion on the matter. 对于那件事意见分歧。', '形容词: divisional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('formal', '[\'fɔːrml]', 'adj.正式的；正规的；形式的；公开的；拘谨的；有条理的', '1. At the formal party I felt very awkward and out of place. 在正式的舞会上，我感到局促不安，很不自在。 2. This job doesn\'t require any formal training. 这种工作不需要任何正规训练。 3. There is only a formal resemblance between the two systems; they are in fact radically different. 这两种体系只是在表面上有某种相似之处，其实根本不同。 4. The writer made a formal denial of the hearsay. 这位作家公开否认了这一传闻。', '副词: formally 名词: formalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lick', '[lɪk]', 'v.舔；轻拍；击败；掠过 n.舔；少许；打；<口>速度', '1. He licked his fingers. 他舔手指。 2. The kitty licked up the milk. 小猫舔光了牛奶。 3. Waves lick the side of a boat. 浪花轻拍着小舟的船舷。 4. It was easy for our team to lick theirs. 我们队很容易打败他们队。 5. He gave the bowl a thorough lick. 他把饭碗舔得一干二净。', '名词: licker 过去式: licked 过去分词: licked 现在分词: licking 第三人称单数: licks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evacuate', '[ɪ\'vækjueɪt]', 'v.疏散；撤出；排泄', '1. There\'s been a bomb threat we need to evacuate. 有人威胁说在这安放了炸弹 我们需要紧急疏散 2. Please evacuate the building immediately. 请立刻自大楼疏散。 3. The first priority shall be to evacuate the bus. 汽车着火后的第一要务是疏散乘客。 4. All people would evacuate the area. 所有人员也都全部撤离这一地区。', '形容词: evacuative 名词: evacuator 过去式: evacuated 过去分词: evacuated 现在分词: evacuating 第三人称单数: evacuates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coordinate', '[koʊ\'ɔːrdɪneɪt]', 'v.（使）协调；（使）一致；（使）同等 n.坐标；同等的人物；配套服装 adj.同等的；等位的；(大学)男女分院制的', '1. You must coordinate the movements of your arms and legs when swimming. 游泳时你必须使臂和腿的动作相协调。 2. If we coordinate our efforts we should be able to win the game. 如果我们同心协力,我们应该能够打赢这场比赛。 3. You must coordinate what you said with what you did. 你必须使你的言行一致。 4. The filter is defined as a box of coordinates. 过滤器定义的是一个方框的坐标。 5. This coordinate system is called the triad at the point. 这个坐标系叫做该点的三面形坐标系。', '形容词: coordinative 副词: coordinately 名词: coordinateness 过去式: coordinated 过去分词: coordinated 现在分词: coordinating 第三人称单数: coordinates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('finally', '[\'faɪnəli]', 'adv.最后；决定性地；最终', '1. Finally the team from Argentina won the championship. 最后，这支来自阿根廷的队伍夺得了冠军。 2. After several delays, he finally set out at 8 o\'clock. 几经耽搁，他终于在八点钟出发了。 3. Finally we got the box out of the door. 最后我们把箱子搬出了门。 4. The patient finally died from cancer. 那位病人最终死于癌症。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trunk', '[trʌŋk]', 'n.树干；(汽车后部)行李箱；大箱子；象鼻；躯干 (复)trunks: 男用运动裤.', '1. The branch has separated from the trunk of the tree. 这个树枝已从树干上脱落了。 2. I eulogize the tall and straight trunk of the white poplar. 我赞美白杨树那挺拔的树干。 3. The trunk is chock-full. There is no more room. 车尾行李箱里塞满了东西。一点空隙都没有了。 4. He crammed all his clothes into the trunk. 他把他所有的衣服硬塞进皮箱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('menu', '[\'menjuː]', 'n.菜单', '1. We only have an a la carte menu. 我们只有分类菜单。 2. He called the waiter to bring the menu. 他叫侍者拿菜单来。 3. I haven\'t decided on the menu yet, let alone bought the food. 我还没决定吃什么菜呢，更不必说买好了。 4. Is fish on the menu today? 今天的菜单上有鱼吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('following', '[\'fɑːloʊɪŋ]', 'adj.接着的；下列的 prep.在 ... 以后 n.追随者；下列各项 动词follow的现在分词', '1. The following item is a piano solo by Jackson. 下一个节目是杰克逊表演的钢琴独奏。 2. It rained on the day we arrived, but the following day was sunny. 我们到达的那天正下雨，但次日天气晴朗。 3. Please choose from the following three selections. 请从下列的三个选择中选择。 4. Following this session,we shall formulate a series of laws. 这次会议以后，要接着制定一系列的法律。 5. Her books aren\'t bestsellers, but they have a certain cult following. 她的书算不上畅销书，但有一定的崇拜者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('syndrome', '[\'sɪndroʊm]', 'n.症候群；综合症', '1. This patient provides a typical example of the syndrome. 这位患者是这种症候群的典型病例。 2. Poor appetite is one of the symptoms of TV syndrome. 食欲不振是电视综合症的症状之一。 3. This syndrome is associated with frequent coughing. 这种综合症与经常咳嗽有关。', '形容词: syndromic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('swift', '[swɪft]', 'adj.快的；迅速的；敏捷的 n.雨燕；线轴 Swift. n.斯威夫特（人名）', '1. His landing is both swift and sure. 他的落地既快又稳。 2. He made a remarkably swift recovery. 他康复得相当快。 3. They\'ve been very swift to deny these rumors. 他们在辟谣方面反应迅速。 4. With the failure of the peace talks, all hopes of a swift end to the war have flown out of the window. 和谈失败后,迅速结束战争的希望都已化为乌有。 5. feel a strong antagonism for sb 6. The Augustan age of English literature includes the writers Dryden, Swift and Pope. 在英国文学的全盛时期 有德莱顿，斯威夫特和蒲柏等文豪。', '副词: swiftly 比较级: swifter 最高级: swiftest 名词: swiftness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('convert', '[kən\'vɜːrt]', 'v.(使)转变；使…改变信仰；转化；兑换；换算 n.皈依者；改变信仰的人', '1. The solar cell can convert the energy of sunlight into electric energy. 太阳能电池能把阳光的能量转化为电能。 2. The old barn we bought to convert into flats was practically tumbling down. 那个旧谷仓我们买下想改建住房的，实际上已经快塌了。 3. My mother has converted to Catholicism. 我母亲已转而信仰天主教。 4. Coal can be converted to gas. 煤可以转化成煤气。 5. He is a recent convert to Christianity. 他最近改信基督教了。', '过去式: converted 过去分词: converted 现在分词: converting 第三人称单数: converts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('affair', '[ə\'fer]', 'n.私通；事件；事务；事情', '1. Their love affair is an open secret. 他们的风流韵事是公开的秘密。 2. The party was a dull affair. 这次聚会单调乏味。 3. The minister is busy with important affairs of state. 部长忙于重要国务。 4. Mind your own affairs! 别管闲事！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evade', '[ɪ\'veɪd]', 'v.逃避；躲避；规避', '1. He could not evade the law. 他逃避不了法律。 2. They evade paying taxes by living abroad. 他们住在国外以逃避交税。 3. In order to evade the persecution of fascists, he had to escape abroad. 为躲避法西斯的迫害，他不得不流徙到国外。 4. Give me a direct answer, and stop evade the issue. 给我一个直截了当的回答，不要回避这一问题。', '形容词: evadable 名词: evader 过去式: evaded 过去分词: evaded 现在分词: evading 第三人称单数: evades');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('down', '[daʊn]', 'adv.向下 prep.沿着 ... 而下 adj.向下的；消沉的；无礼的 n.绒毛；汗毛 v.击倒；打败；吞下；被抑制', '1. Please sit down. 请坐下。 2. He is walking down the seaside. 他正沿海边走去。 3. I\'ve been feeling down since I lost my job. 自从失去工作後,我的情绪一直处於低潮。 4. She\'s terribly down on people who don\'t do things her way. 她对不按她的要求做事的人十分不满。 5. A quilt stuffed with the down of the eider duck. 这条被子是用绒鸭毛做芯子的。 6. Antiaircraft guns downed three bombers. 高射炮击落了三架轰炸机。', '过去式: downed 过去分词: downed 现在分词: downing 第三人称单数: downs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quiver', '[\'kwɪvər]', 'v.颤抖；振动 n.颤抖；箭袋；箭袋内的箭', '1. The old man quivered with rage. 这位老人气得发抖。 2. The skylark quivered its wings. 云雀抖动它的双翼。 3. There was a slight quiver in his voice as he spoke. 他说话时声音有些颤抖。 4. A quiver of fear ran through her. 一阵恐惧的颤抖传遍了她的全身。', '形容词: quivery 过去式: quivered 过去分词: quivered 现在分词: quivering 第三人称单数: quivers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('queer', '[kwɪr]', 'adj.古怪的；奇怪的；可疑的；<俚>同性恋的 n.<俚>同性恋者 vt.把...弄糟；使陷入不利', '1. There is something queer about him. 他有些古怪。 2. Her queer way of dressing attracted the attention of the passerby. 她古怪的着装方式引起了过路人的注意。 3. I have a queer dream last night. 我昨晚做了一个奇怪的梦。 4. I heard some very queer noises in the garden. 我听到花园里有些可疑的声音。 5. His blunder would certainly queer his chances of promotion. 他犯的大错肯定会毁了他晋升的机会。', '形容词: queerish 副词: queerly 比较级: queerer 最高级: queerest 名词: queerness 过去式: queered 过去分词: queered 现在分词: queering 第三人称单数: queers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gymnasium', '[dʒɪm\'neɪziəm]', 'n.体育馆；健身房 (复数）gymnasia或gymnasiums.', '1. The child somersaulted across the gymnasium. 那孩子翻著跟头从体育馆这头翻到那头。 2. A new gymnasium has been built on our campus. 我们大学的校园里新建了一座体育馆。 3. Our gymnasium lacks sports facilities. 我们的健身房缺少运动器材。 4. He go to the gymnasium to practise every day. 他每天都去健身房训练。', '名词复数: gymnasiums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intelligence', '[ɪn\'telɪdʒəns]', 'n.智力；理解力 n.情报；情报工作；情报机关', '1. She\'s the equal of her brother as far as intelligence is concerned. 论智力，她和她哥哥不相上下。 2. His intelligence is rather limited. 他的智力相当有限。 3. She\'s not lacking in intelligence. 她并不缺乏学识。 4. Our intelligence shows that the enemy is advancing. 我们的情报显示敌人正在向前推进。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('panel', '[\'pænl]', 'n.嵌板；仪表盘；面板；座谈小组；陪审团 v.嵌镶', '1. The builders set the panel in carefully. 建筑工人把嵌板小心地镶上去。 2. The worker will check functions of instrument panel. 工人将检查仪表盘功能。 3. Solar panels are used to power satellites. 太阳能面板用来给卫星提供动力。 4. The date for the panel discussion is fixed now. 座谈会的日期现已确定。 5. He panelled the wall with wood. 他在墙上镶上木板。', '过去式: paneled/panelled 过去分词: paneled/panelled 现在分词: paneling/panelling 第三人称单数: panels/panels');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accountant', '[ə\'kaʊntənt]', 'n.会计人员；会计师', '1. He was deep in conversation with his accountant. 他与会计深入交谈。 2. The accountant described his work to the sales staff. 那个会计向营业部的职员介绍了自己的工作情况。 3. The company accountant queried my travel expenses. 公司的会计对我的旅行开支提出疑问。 4. The book is kept by a freelance accountant. 由独立会计师进行计帐。', '名词: accountancy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('distract', '[dɪ\'strækt]', 'vt.分散；转移；分心；困扰', '1. The film managed to distract me from these problems for a while. 这部影片分散了我的注意力，让我暂时忘记了这些难题。 2. It was all a ploy to distract attention from his real aims. 那纯粹是障眼法，用以分散人们对他真正意图的注意力。 3. We must change our route to distract the attention of the enemy. 我们必须改变行军路线以转移敌人的注意力。 4. Once she gets involved in a research, nothing can distract her mind from it. 她一旦潜心钻研某一课题,任何事情都无法使她分心。', '形容词: distractive 副词: distractingly 过去式: distracted 过去分词: distracted 现在分词: distracting 第三人称单数: distracts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scout', '[skaʊt]', 'n.童子军；侦察员；守卫 vt.侦察；物色', '1. I remember when I used to be a Girl Scout. 我记得我还是一名女童子军的时候。 2. The scout spurred on to the destination. 侦察员向目的地疾驰而去。 3. The scout was searching through the woods. 侦察员正在树林中搜索。 4. Three planes were sent up to scout. 派出三架飞机侦察。', '名词: scouter 过去式: scouted 过去分词: scouted 现在分词: scouting 第三人称单数: scouts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('final', '[\'faɪnl]', 'adj.最终的；最后的；决定性的；不可改变的 n.决赛；大学毕业考试；期终考试', '1. The proposal was presented as final package deal. 那项建议是作为最终的一揽子交易提出来的。 2. We are all satisfied with the final result. 我们都对最终的结果感到满意。 3. This is our final offer. 这是我方的最后报价。 4. The game is now in its final stages. 这场比赛现在处于最后阶段。 5. The World Cup final is being transmitted live to over fifty countries. 世界杯决赛现在正向五十多个国家现场转播。', '副词: finally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mourn', '[mɔːrn]', 'v.哀悼；忧伤；服丧', '1. People wore crapes to mourn our leader. 人们戴着黑纱哀悼我们的领导。 2. We mourn for our fallen soldiers. 我们哀悼阵亡的兵士。 3. The old woman still mourns for her son. 这位老太太还在为儿子的死伤心。 4. We mourn in black. 我们穿黑色衣服服丧。', '副词: mourningly 名词: mourner 过去式: mourned 过去分词: mourned 现在分词: mourning 第三人称单数: mourns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wedge', '[wedʒ]', 'n.楔子；楔形物 vt.楔住；嵌；挤进', '1. Put a wedge under the door so that it will stay open. 在门底下塞一块楔子，让门保持开着。 2. The attackers formed a wedge and plowed through the enemy line. 进攻者形成了一个楔子，突破了敌军的阵线 3. He had a banana and a wedge of cheese for lunch. 他中饭吃一根香蕉和一块楔形的奶酪。 4. Please wedge this cabinet to keep it from tipping. 请在橱底楔入楔子以防它倾斜。', '过去式: wedged 过去分词: wedged 现在分词: wedging 第三人称单数: wedges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('razor', '[\'reɪzər]', 'n.剃刀', '1. He shaved his face with a razor. 他用剃刀刮脸。 2. He was honing his razor although it\'s very sharp. 尽管他的剃刀十分锋利了，可他还是不停地磨它。 3. This electric razor is our latest promotion. 这种电剃刀是我们的最新产品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('succession', '[sək\'seʃn]', 'n.连续；继承权；继位', '1. He was late for school three times in succession. 他连续三次上学迟到。 2. He retrieved his losses by betting on a succession of winners. 他下的赌注连续获胜才挽回了损失。 3. The cost of living seems set to drop for the third month in succession. 生活费用持续下降，眼看就快三个月了。 4. There was a dispute about the rightful succession to the throne. 对于王位的合法继承权有过一场争论。', '形容词: successional 副词: successionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('except', '[ɪk\'sept]', 'prep.除了 ... 之外 conj.除非；除了 ... 之外；若不是 vt.除；除外', '1. They all went to sleep except me. 除我之外，他们都去睡觉了。 2. It\'s a poor tune, except to be dancing to. 这支曲子不好,除非用它作舞蹈的伴奏曲。 3. They didn\'t open their mouths except to complain. 除了抱怨他们从不开口 4. I would buy the suit,except that it cost too much. 如果不是它价格太高的话,我本想买下那件衣服。 5. You will all be punished; I can except no one. 你们全得受罚,我一个也不饶。', '过去式: excepted 过去分词: excepted 现在分词: excepting 第三人称单数: excepts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('superficial', '[ˌsuːpər\'fɪʃl]', 'adj.表面的；肤浅的', '1. Superficial scratches can be easily removed. 表面的划痕很容易擦掉。 2. A superficial injury is not serious. 表面的伤不太严重。 3. This is only superficial prosperity. 这只是表面繁荣。 4. He is too superficial to appreciate great literature like this. 他太肤浅，无法欣赏这类文学巨著。', '副词: superficially 名词: superficiality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('October', '[ɑːk\'toʊbər]', 'n.十月', '1. His book is due to be published in October. 他的书预定十月份出版。 2. October the first is the National Day of China. 十月一日是中国的国庆节。 3. Leaves begin to fall in October. 十月里树叶开始落下。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dump', '[dʌmp]', 'vt.倾倒；抛弃；倾销；抛售；倾卸；[计]转储 vi.倾倒；突然落下 n.垃圾场；军需供应站', '1. Some people just dump their rubbish in the river. 有些人径直往河里倒垃圾。 2. Sealed containers of nuclear waste have been dumped in the sea. 盛有核废料的密封容器被丢在海里。 3. They dump surplus goods abroad. 他们向国外倾销过剩货物。 4. A complete memory dump file is rarely required. 通常很少需要完全内存转储文件。 5. You\'ll be fined if you dump here. 在这儿倒垃圾要被罚款的。 6. There is a refuse dump out of the town. 镇外有个垃圾场。', '名词: dumper 过去式: dumped 过去分词: dumped 现在分词: dumping 第三人称单数: dumps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pea', '[piː]', 'n.豌豆', '1. This kind of pea has a long pod. 这种豌豆长着长豆荚。 2. Pea pods burst open when overripe. 豌豆过熟就会爆裂。 3. We have a bowl of very salty pea and ham soup. 我们喝了一碗非常咸的豌豆火腿汤。 4. The sisters are as alike as two peas. 两姐妹长得一模一样。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tar', '[tɑːr]', 'n. 焦油； 柏油 n. <口>水手 vt. 涂以焦油', '1. This kind of tobacco has a high tar content. 这种香烟焦油含量很高。 2. Tar is much used in making modern roads. 修建现代公路多用焦油沥青。 3. I had to tar the driveway in the afternoon. 我得在下午把车道涂上柏油。 4. Tar is a binder for gravel in paving. 在铺路时柏油用来黏结砾石。', '过去式: tarred 过去分词: tarred 现在分词: tarring 第三人称单数: tars');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('succeed', '[sək\'siːd]', 'v.成功；继承；接着发生', '1. If you work hard you will succeed. 如果你努力工作，你就会成功。 2. We succeeded in repairing the engine. 我们成功地修好了发动机。 3. When the duke dies, his eldest son will succeed to the title. 公爵去世之后，他的长子将继承他的爵位。 4. The war ended and a long peace succeeded. 战争结束之后紧接着是长期的和平。', '形容词: succedent 名词: succeeder 过去式: succeeded 过去分词: succeeded 现在分词: succeeding 第三人称单数: succeeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bear', '[ber]', 'n.熊 v.忍受；负荷；结果；证实；生子女', '1. The hunter slashed at the bear with his knife. 猎人挥刀向熊猛烈砍去。 2. The bear has lived up to his reputation for stupidity. 这只熊果然名不虚传，笨得出奇。 3. I can\'t bear young people casting away their youth. 我无法忍受年轻人虚掷青春。 4. Girls whom can get easily may be hard to bear. 容易追求的女子,也许很难忍受。', '过去式: bore 过去分词: borne/born 现在分词: bearing 第三人称单数: bears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blame', '[bleɪm]', 'vt.责备；把 ... 归咎于 n.责备；过失', '1. The driver was not to blame for the accident. 这次事故怪不着司机。 2. The bank manager was really to blame, though he tried to pin it on a clerk. 真正受责备的应该是银行经理，可是他却想把责任推到一个职员身上。 3. She blamed him for the failure of their marriage. 她把婚姻的触礁归咎於他。 4. They blamed the rise in oil prices for the big increase in inflation. 他们把通货膨胀大幅度增长归咎于石油价格的上涨。 5. We were ready to take the blame for what had happened. 我们准备对所发生的事承担责任。', '名词: blamer 过去式: blamed 过去分词: blamed 现在分词: blaming 第三人称单数: blames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('half', '[hæf]', 'n.一半；下半场；半学年 adj.一半的；不完全的 adv.一半地；不完全地', '1. Half of them are here. 半数人来了。 2. At best we can do only half as much as last year. 我们至多只能做到去年的一半。 3. The game didn\'t heat up until the second half. 游戏玩到后半场才热闹起来。 4. The team recovered its lead in the second half. 该队在下半场重新领先。 5. Half the car was damaged. 车子毁了一半。 6. The girl left her homework half done. 这女孩只做完了一半作业。', '名词复数: halves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sure', '[ʃʊr]', 'adj.肯定的；确信的；必定；可靠的；沉着自信的 adv.当然；确实地；无疑地；不用客气', '1. I think you are not quite sure about it. 我认为,你们对这一点并不能完全肯定。 2. I\'m sure you\'ll want a go when you see it. 我敢说你看到了就想试一下。 3. I can\'t be sure, but I believe it worths trying. 我不能确定,但我确信这值得一试。 4. The news is sure to overset him. 这条消息必定会使他心神不安。 5. It sure was a cold night. 的确是个寒冷的夜晚。', NULL);
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('preposition', '[ˌprepə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.介词', '1. Preposition is abbreviated as \"prep\" in this dictionary. 介词在词典中略作 “prep”。 2. Avoid ending a sentence with a preposition. 避免用介词结束一个句子。 3. You should cancel this preposition in the sentence. 你应该删去句子中的这个介系词。 4. The verb\"abide\"is construed with the preposition\"by\". 动词abide与介词by连用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('welfare', '[\'welfer]', 'n.福利；福利事业；幸福', '1. The welfare of the individual is bound up with the welfare of the community. 个人的福利与社会的福利有着密切的关系。 2. These are matters that bear on the welfare of the community. 这些都是与社会福利有关的问题。 3. The government decided to promote public welfare. 政府决定发展公共福利。 4. My principal concern is my family\'s welfare. 我至为关心的是我一家的幸福。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mutual', '[\'mjuːtʃuəl]', 'adj.共同的；相互的', '1. Other organizations have joined the confederation for mutual benefit. 其他组织为了共同的利益也加入了这个联盟。 2. My friend and I have mutual enthusiasm for music. 我和我的朋友对音乐有着共同的爱好。 3. Let\'s give mutual support and inspiration to each other. 让我们互相支持，互相鼓励。 4. Language differences are often a barrier to mutual understanding. 语言不同,常常阻碍到彼此的了解。', '副词: mutually 名词: mutuality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beef', '[biːf]', 'n.牛肉；肌肉；力气；牢骚 v.抱怨；告发；加强', '1. Do you like stewed beef? 你喜欢吃炖牛肉吗？ 2. Africa is exporting beef to Europe. 非洲向欧洲出口牛肉。 3. He\'s got plenty of beef. 他肌肉发达。 4. My beef is that it took too much time. 我的抱怨是太花时间了。 5. He is forever beefing about that. 他没完没了地为那事抱怨。', '名词复数: beeves 过去式: beefed 过去分词: beefed 现在分词: beefing 第三人称单数: beefs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scorn', '[skɔːrn]', 'n.轻蔑；奚落；笑柄 v.轻蔑；鄙视；嘲弄；不屑', '1. He eyed me with a terrible scorn. 他极其轻蔑地打量着我。 2. He spat out the words with scorn. 他用轻蔑的口吻说了这番话。 3. He were to become a mark of public scorn. 他将成为公众奚落的典型。 4. The loser\'s scorn for the award is pure sour grape. 失败者对奖品的轻视纯粹是吃不到葡萄说葡萄酸。 5. You\'ve no right to scorn a poor girl. 你没有权利藐视一个穷女孩。', '形容词: scornful 副词: scornfully 名词: scorner 过去式: scorned 过去分词: scorned 现在分词: scorning 第三人称单数: scorns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('potential', '[pə\'tenʃl]', 'adj.潜在的；可能的 n.潜力；潜能 n.电位；电势', '1. These potential effects must be studied carefully. 这些潜在的影响必须仔细地加以研究。 2. Aha! Now that \'s something that has potential . 啊！ 现在这好像是很有可能的。 3. She has acting potential, but she needs training. 她有表演潜力，但需要训练。 4. He hasn\'t realized his full potential yet. 他还没有意识到他的全部潜能。 5. We can only measure the difference between the potentials of two half cells when they are linked to form an electrochemical cell. 当两个半电池连接形成一个化学电池时,我们仅能测定两个半电池之间电位的差值。', '副词: potentially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('issue', '[\'ɪʃuː]', 'n.议题；问题；期刊号；一次发行额；发行；<律>子女 v.发表；公布；正式发给；发行；流出', '1. You\'re just avoiding the issue. 你只不过是在回避问题。 2. The union plans to raise the issue of overtime. 工会打算提出加班的问题。 3. Parliament will debate the nationalization issue next week. 议会将在下周辩论国有化议题。 4. They make an issue of this with UEFA. 他们就此向欧足联提出上诉。 5. Xinhua News Agency is authorized to issue the following statement. 新华社受权发表如下声明。', '形容词: issueless 名词: issuer 过去式: issued 过去分词: issued 现在分词: issuing 第三人称单数: issues');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('coffee', '[\'kɔːfi]', 'n.咖啡；咖啡色', '1. He put some sugar into his coffee. 他往咖啡里加了些糖。 2. Have some cream in your coffee. 在你的咖啡里加点奶油吧。 3. We had cookies and coffee. 我们吃了甜饼和咖啡。 4. I prefer tea to coffee. 我更喜欢茶，而不是咖啡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chancellor', '[\'tʃænsələr]', 'n.大臣；总理；名誉校长；大法官', '1. He was England\'s worst Chancellor of the Exchequer. 他是英国最糟糕的财政大臣。 2. The knives are out for the chancellor. 要对这位大臣兴师问罪了。 3. The Chancellor will present his budget to Parliament tomorrow. 总理明天将在会议上提出他的预算案。 4. The move welcomed by German Chancellor Angela Merkel. 此举受到德国总理默克尔欢迎。', '名词: chancellorship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eastern', '[\'iːstərn]', 'adj.东部的；东方的', '1. The eastern situation is similarly intense. 东部的情况同样紧张。 2. A road leads through the eastern commercial hub of Bukavu, Congo. 一条马路穿过刚果布卡武东部的商业区。 3. Eastern Gnosticism took a somewhat different course. 东方的诺斯替派有些不同的实践。 4. The mountain was clearly defined against the eastern sky. 山巅被东方的天际衬托得轮廓格外分明。', '名词: easternness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('thank', '[θæŋk]', 'v.感谢；谢谢；责怪 n.谢意；感谢', '1. Thank you all the same. 不管怎样，还是要谢谢你。 2. I don\'t know how I can possibly thank you enough. 我不知道该怎样来感谢你才好。 3. I\'d like to take this opportunity to thank everyone for their hard work on the project. 我愿借此机会感谢每一位为这个项目辛勤工作的人。 4. Thank God, grant me a good friend. 谢谢上帝，赐给我一个好朋友。 5. Please convey my thank to your wife. 请向你的妻子转达我的谢意。', '过去式: thanked 过去分词: thanked 现在分词: thanking 第三人称单数: thanks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('force', '[fɔːrs]', 'n.武力；暴力；力量；影响力；力量大的人或（事物）；权力；（为某目的组织起来的）一群人；军队；部队；武装力量；警察部门；力；风力 v.迫使；强迫；强制；使发生；强装（欢笑）；人工催长', '1. When persuasion failed they used force. 劝说无效时,他们就使用武力了。 2. We\'ll settle the problem by force if necessary. 如果有必要的话,我们会用武力解决这个问题。 3. If you do not open the door, I am authorized to enter by use of force. 如果你不开门,我有权使用暴力闯入。 4. It is vain to attempt to root out heresy by force. 试图用暴力消除异端邪说是徒劳的。 5. Circumstances force us to adopt this policy. 形势迫使我们采取这项政策。', '形容词: forceable 名词: forcer 过去式: forced 过去分词: forced 现在分词: forcing 第三人称单数: forces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('immense', '[ɪ\'mens]', 'adj.巨大的；广大的；<口>非常好的', '1. They plunged into their work with immense zeal. 他们以极大的热情投入工作。 2. Her contributions to the state have been immense. 她对国家的贡献极大。 3. It\'s almost impossible to find him in the immense ocean. 在无边无际的海洋中要找到他几乎是不可能的。 4. It were the new comers who had cultivated the immense wilderness. 初来此地的人开辟了这片广袤的荒野。', '副词: immensely 名词: immenseness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accident', '[\'æksɪdənt]', 'n.事故；意外；偶然；造化', '1. His left knee was hurt in a traffic accident. 他的左膝在一次交通事故中受伤了。 2. Happily, the accident was prevented. 很幸运，事故得以避免了。 3. The other day I came across an interesting accident. 几天前,我碰到一件意外事情。 4. I started the hobby almost by accident. 我有了这个爱好纯属偶然。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quick', '[kwɪk]', 'adj.迅速的；快的；机敏的 adv.迅速地；快', '1. Everyone is trying to get rich quick nowadays. 现在每个人都想要尽快发财致富。 2. He gave a quick answer to the teacher\'s question. 他对老师的提问作出了迅速的回答。 3. They are pressing us to make a quick decision. 他们正在敦促我们迅速作出决定。 4. Come on quick or we\'ll be left behind. 快，不然我们就掉队了。 5. He antidoted the poison with quick medication. 他迅速地用药物解毒。', '副词: quickly 比较级: quicker 最高级: quickest 名词: quickness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pierce', '[pɪrs]', 'v.刺穿；穿透；洞悉 Pierce. n.皮尔斯（人名）', '1. The needle pierced her finger. 针刺进了她的手指。 2. This new type of bullet can pierce armor. 这种新型子弹头能够穿甲。 3. Her shrieks pierced the air. 她尖锐的叫声直刺云天。 4. The regiment pierced through the enemy\'s lines. 这个团突破了敌军防线。', '形容词: piercing 副词: piercingly 名词: piercer 过去式: pierced 过去分词: pierced 现在分词: piercing 第三人称单数: pierces');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spear', '[spɪr]', 'n.矛；标枪 v.刺穿', '1. The fisher used a spear as his weapon. 渔夫用矛作为武器。 2. The hunter hurled his spear at the tiger. 猎人用力把他的长矛向虎投去。 3. The spear curved through the air. 标枪在空中沿曲线运动。 4. The athlete is trying to launch a spear. 运动员正在用力投掷标枪。 5. They were standing in the river spearing fish. 他们站在河里叉鱼。', '形容词: spearlike 名词: spearer 过去式: speared 过去分词: speared 现在分词: spearing 第三人称单数: spears');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('relax', '[rɪ\'læks]', 'v.休息；放松；使 ... 放松；放宽', '1. I just want to sit down and relax. 我只想坐下休息会。 2. I felt my shoulders relax a little. 我觉得我的肩膀放松了好多。 3. His muscles relaxed. 他的肌肉松弛了。 4. A good massage will relax your tired muscles. 舒服的按摩会让你疲惫的肌肉放松。', '形容词: relaxable 过去式: relaxed 过去分词: relaxed 现在分词: relaxing 第三人称单数: relaxes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('communicate', '[kə\'mjuːnɪkeɪt]', 'v.传达；沟通；交流', '1. He has communicated his wishes to me. 他已经把他的愿望告诉了我。 2. I like to communicate with my family. 我喜欢和我的家人沟通。 3. The door communicates with my room. 这门和我的房间相通。 4. Good manners are not only about the way we talk, but also about all other things we do when we communicate with other people. 好的礼节不仅仅是指我们谈话的方式,还包括我们在与别人交流时进行各种活动的处理办法与态度。', '名词: communicator 过去式: communicated 过去分词: communicated 现在分词: communicating 第三人称单数: communicates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('closet', '[\'klɑːzət]', 'n.壁橱；衣帽间；密室；厕所 adj.隐藏的；不公开的；空谈的 vt.把 ... 关在房间里', '1. Put the coats back into the closet. 请把大衣放回到壁橱里。 2. You may put these books in the closet. 你可以把这些书放在壁橱里。 3. The Prince\'s bedroom is large, but his closet is larger. 王子的卧室也很大,不过他的衣帽间则更大。 4. The loser closely enclosed himself in the closet. 那个失败者把自己严密地封闭在小室内。 5. We must guard against closet racists. 我们必须警惕隐蔽的种族主义者。 6. He used to closet himself with a book. 过去他常把自己关在小房间里读书。', '名词: closetful 过去式: closeted 过去分词: closeted 现在分词: closeting 第三人称单数: closets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beside', '[bɪ\'saɪd]', 'prep.在 ... 旁边；与 ... 相比；和... 无关', '1. I set a chair beside him and sat down. 我在他旁边放了一把椅子然后坐下了。 2. The little girl is sitting beside her mother. 小女孩正坐在她妈妈旁边。 3. Our achievements seem small beside his. 与他的成就相比我们的就显得微不足道了。 4. Money seems unimportant when setting beside the joys of family life. 与天伦之乐相比,金钱显得微不足道。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('charm', '[tʃɑːrm]', 'n.魅力；吸引力；迷人；美貌 v.（使）着迷；施魔法', '1. Her charm rests in her happy smile. 她的魅力在于她幸福的微笑。 2. The use of dialect lent great charm to the work . 方言的运用给这部作品增添了巨大的魅力。 3. The hotel is full of charm and character. 这家旅馆风格独特，极具吸引力。 4. Her charm prejudiced the judges in her favour. 她姿色迷人，因而评委都偏向她。 5. He guessed the idea would charm his publisher. 他认为这个主意能让他的出版商着迷。', '形容词: charmless 副词: charmingly 过去式: charmed 过去分词: charmed 现在分词: charming 第三人称单数: charms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('litter', '[\'lɪtər]', 'n.垃圾；杂乱；一窝(幼仔)；褥草；轿子 v.乱丢垃圾；弄乱；产(幼仔)；用草等给动物铺窝', '1. There was litter strewn all over the pavement. 人行道上到处都是扔的垃圾。 2. The desk was covered with a litter of documents. 书桌上满满地放着一堆杂乱的文件。 3. His litter strewn room really needed to be cleaned. 他杂乱的房间该好好收拾一下了。 4. His dog hasn\'t had a litter of puppies. 他的狗还没有生过一窝小狗。', '名词: litterer 过去式: littered 过去分词: littered 现在分词: littering 第三人称单数: litters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tangle', '[\'tæŋɡl]', 'n.缠结；混乱；纠纷 vt.使缠结；使混乱；使陷入 vi.纠缠；乱作一团；<口>吵架；争论', '1. The wool got in a fearful tangle. 毛线乱成了一团。 2. His financial affairs are in such a tangle. 他的钱财是糊涂帐。 3. We employed a lawyer to straighten our legal tangle. 我们雇了一位律师把法律纠纷理出头绪。 4. The little girl tangled the yarn her mother was knitting. 小女孩把她妈妈在编结的毛线弄得纠结在一起了。 5. He was really a tough guy to tangle with. 他真是一个难缠的人。', '形容词: tangly 过去式: tangled 过去分词: tangled 现在分词: tangling 第三人称单数: tangles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chap', '[tʃæp]', 'n. 皲裂 n. 颌； 颊 n. <口>小伙子； 家伙 v. 皲裂； （皮肤)变粗糙 abbr. 章（=chapter）', '1. The poor chap was a bundle of nerves at the interview. 这小子在面试时紧张极了。 2. There are lots of remedies to give your lips chap defense. 防止嘴唇皲裂有很多方法。 3. The chap\'s countenance was yellow and fleshless, and the dented cheeks had accented his nose to be as high and straight as that of a Greek. 小伙子脸色黄瘦，而且两颊有点塌陷，显得鼻子象希腊人一样又高又直。 4. Nobody knew who had cooled that chap off. 没有人知道是谁干掉那个家伙的。 5. My lips chap in this dry weather. 在这种干燥的气候下，我的嘴唇皲裂了。', '过去式: chapped 过去分词: chapped 现在分词: chapping 第三人称单数: chaps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('acquaintance', '[ə\'kweɪntəns]', 'n.熟人；相识；了解', '1. He is not a friend of mine, only an acquaintance. 他不是朋友我的,只是个熟人。 2. I made his acquaintance at a party. 我是在一次聚会上认识他的。 3. Their acquaintance was of long standing. 他们相识多年。 4. He has only a limited acquaintance with the matter. 他对这件事的了解很有限。', '名词: acquaintanceship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('provision', '[prə\'vɪʒn]', 'n.食品；粮食；供应；规定；条款；预备；【经】准备金 vt.向 ... 供应食物', '1. We set out with enough provisions. 我们带上足够的食品出发了。 2. Provision of shelter was the Red Crosss main concern for the disaster victims. 为灾民提供避难处是 红十字会的主要工作。 3. The present law makes no provision for this. 现行的法律对此未作任何规定。 4. Both sides should act according to the provisions of the agreement. 双方都应按协议条款办事。 5. They provisioned the ship for a long voyage. 他们为远航的船只准备了食品和必需品。', '名词: provisioner 过去式: provisioned 过去分词: provisioned 现在分词: provisioning 第三人称单数: provisions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('employ', '[ɪm\'plɔɪ]', 'v.雇佣；使用', '1. They employ casual labor to pick the fruit 他们雇佣临时工摘水果。 2. You must employ someone to oversee the project. 你得雇个人监督这一工程。 3. Why do you think we should employ you? 你认为我们为何要雇佣你? 4. Different artists employ different painting techniques. 不同的画家会使用不同的绘画技巧。', '形容词: employable 名词: employability 过去式: employed 过去分词: employed 现在分词: employing 第三人称单数: employs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('origin', '[\'ɔːrɪdʒɪn]', 'n.起源；出身；[数]原点；起因', '1. The social unrest has its origins in economic problems. 社会动荡是经济问题引起的。 2. This is the true story of the weeds: the origin of the species. 这是一个关于野草的真实故事:关于他们的物种起源。 3. He is a Dane by origin. 他原籍丹麦。 4. The family had its origin in Canada. 这家祖上是加拿大人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diploma', '[dɪ\'ploʊmə]', 'n.文凭', '1. He obtained a diploma in architecture. 他获得了建筑学的学位证书。 2. The youth won his diploma after only three years. 那青年仅用了3 年时间就取得毕业文凭。 3. When a person has successfully completed a certain course of study, he is given a diploma by the school. 当一个人成功地完成了某一课程的研读,学校将授予他一张文凭。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('snow', '[snoʊ]', 'n.雪；积雪；下雪 vi.下雪 vt.使变白；雪覆盖', '1. Snow scattered unequally over the mountainside. 雪不均匀地散落在山腰上。 2. The compacted snow on the pavement turned to ice. 人行道上被踩实的雪已变成了冰。 3. He trudge three hour in the snow to get back home. 他在雪中跋涉三个钟点才回到家。 4. Last winter the snow lay thick on the ground. 去年冬天，地上积雪很厚。 5. It was snowing heavily. 天正在下大雪。 6. The highway was covered with snow. 公路被雪覆盖著。', '过去式: snowed 过去分词: snowed 现在分词: snowing 第三人称单数: snows');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('realm', '[relm]', 'n.领域；王国', '1. They exist only in the physical realm. 它们只存在于物质感官的领域。 2. He made outstanding contributions in the realm of foreign affairs. 他在外交领域作出了卓越贡献。 3. The material realm is one area that everyone relates to. 物质领域是与每个人有联系的一个地方。 4. He was banished from the realm. 他被驱逐出境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('require', '[rɪ\'kwaɪər]', 'v.要求；需要；命令；规定', '1. The director required that we should work all night. 主任要求我们通宵工作。 2. We must not propagate one method and require all localities to adopt it. 我们在宣传上不要只讲一种办法，要求各地都照着去做。 3. Please call if you require assistance. 如果需要帮忙，请打电话。 4. This game requires a minimum of three players. 这个游戏至少需要三个人才可以玩。', '形容词: requirable 名词: requirer 过去式: required 过去分词: required 现在分词: requiring 第三人称单数: requires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sword', '[sɔːrd]', 'n.剑；刀', '1. He drove at her with his sword. 他用剑猛攻击她。 2. He is slashing wildly at his opponent with a sword. 他正用剑疯狂地朝对手乱砍。 3. The officer belted his sword on. 军官用皮带扣住佩刀。 4. The robber thrust his sword through the traveler\'s bosom. 那强盗以刀刺穿了那旅客的胸部。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crust', '[krʌst]', 'n.外壳；坚硬的外壳；面包皮 vt.盖以硬皮 vi.结硬皮', '1. The earth\'s crust is layered.. 地球的外壳是分层的。 2. The crust on the snow was thick enough for us to walk on it. 外层的雪已经冻硬，可以在上面行走。 3. Please cut the bread into slices and remove the crust. 请将面包切片并去除外壳。 4. The crust of the bread is burnt. 这块面包的外皮烤焦了。 5. The snow crusted the lake last night. 昨夜的雪使湖面结了冰。 6. The snow may crust at night, due to outward radiation. 由于外部辐射，晚上雪可能结成雪壳。', '形容词: crustless 过去式: crusted 过去分词: crusted 现在分词: crusting 第三人称单数: crusts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('liberty', '[\'lɪbərti]', 'n.自由；自由权；冒失', '1. Those prisoners are dreaming of liberty. 这些囚犯们梦想着获得自由。 2. Everybody is at liberty to air his views. 每个人都有发表意见的自由。 3. Women used to have little liberty. 过去妇女没有多少自由。 4. I am afraid that I am not at liberty to discuss this matter. 对不起，我无权讨论这个问题。', '名词复数: liberties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tomorrow', '[tə\'mɔːroʊ]', 'adv.明天 n.明天；将来', '1. We will play basketball tomorrow. 我们明天打篮球。 2. I will take an examination tomorrow. 明天我将参加一场考试。 3. If weather permits, we will go to the park tomorrow. 如果天气好的话,明天我们去公园。 4. I bought some buns for tomorrow\'s breakfast. 我买了几个圆面包当明天的早餐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('layman', '[\'leɪmən]', 'n.俗人(对僧侣而言)；门外汉', '1. He is a layman in politics. 他对政治是个门外汉。 2. This book is written for professionals and laymen alike. 这本书既可供专业人员阅读，又可供外行人看。 3. Where the law is concerned, I am only a layman. 谈到法律, 我不过是门外汉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('powder', '[\'paʊdər]', 'n.粉末；粉；火药；细雪 vt.洒粉于；使变成粉；重击 vi.变成粉；涂粉', '1. Borax is a kind of white powder. 硼砂是一种白色粉末。 2. There\'s too much powder on your nose. 你鼻子上的粉擦得太多了。 3. I know the smell of powder. 我上过战场。 4. Have you ever skied the powder in Utah? 你在犹他州滑过雪吗? 5. I\'m just going to powder my nose. 我想去补补妆。 6. Actors powder with their left hands for luck. 演员们为了讨吉利而用左手搽粉。', '名词: powderer 过去式: powdered 过去分词: powdered 现在分词: powdering 第三人称单数: powders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('corner', '[\'kɔːrnər]', 'n.角落；转角；困境 v.将 ... 逼入困境；转弯；垄断 adj.位于角落的', '1. The news soon spread to the farthest corner. 消息很快传到最远的角落。 2. She sat in the corner, watching my every move. 她坐在角落里注视著我的一举一动。 3. She waved to me as she turned the corner. 她拐弯时向我挥了挥手。 4. There\'s a grocer\'s at the corner of the street. 在街道的转弯处有一个食品杂货店。 5. Don\'t try to corner your spouse. 不要让你的爱人为难。 6. She bought a box of chocolates at the corner store. 她在街头小店购得一盒巧克力。', '过去式: cornered 过去分词: cornered 现在分词: cornering 第三人称单数: corners');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('chalk', '[tʃɔːk]', 'n.粉笔；白垩 v.用粉笔写；记录；使变白；归咎', '1. The teacher wrote on the blackboard with a piece of chalk. 老师用一支粉笔在黑板上写字。 2. The teacher\'s chalk grated on the blackboard. 老师的粉笔在黑板上发出刺耳的摩擦声。 3. My father said cement couldn\'t be made from chalk. 我父亲说水泥不能用白垩来制作。 4. The boys chalked out goalposts on the playground wall. 男孩子们在运动场的墙上用粉笔画上了球门柱。', '形容词: chalky 名词: chalkiness 过去式: chalked 过去分词: chalked 现在分词: chalking 第三人称单数: chalks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wake', '[weɪk]', 'v.醒来；唤醒；意识到 n.航迹；守夜', '1. I usually wake up early. 我通常醒得很早。 2. She spends all her waking hours worrying about her job. 她只要醒著就一直为工作发愁。 3. The incident woke memories of his past sufferings. 这件事唤起了他对过去苦难经历的回忆。 4. Only you, can wake up Snow White! 只有你能唤醒公主！ 5. We just saw the foaming white wake of the liner. w我们只看到班轮驶过留下的白沫翻腾的航迹。', '名词: waker 过去式: woke/waked 过去分词: waked/woken 现在分词: waking 第三人称单数: wakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wind', '[wɪnd]', 'n.风；（随食物或饮料）吞下的气；呼吸；气息；管乐器；<口>空谈 v.使喘不过气来；（给婴儿轻轻拍抚后背）使打嗝；吹(号角等)；（路、河等）蜿蜒；缠绕；给…上发条；可上发条；倒（磁带、胶卷等）；转动（把手） n.弯曲；弯曲处；缠绕；转动；上发条', '1. A gust of wind blew my hat off. 一阵大风吹走了我的帽子。 2. The higher the tree, the stronger the wind. 树越高, 风越大。 3. The day was very still, without a breath of wind. 天空十分平静 4. I can\'t eat beans--they give me wind. 我不能吃豆子，吃了肚子就胀气。 5. He was momentarily winded by the blow to his stomach. 他的肚子上挨了一击，一时喘不过气来。 6. Give the handle another couple of winds. 再转动两下手柄。', '名词: winder 过去式: winded 过去分词: winded 现在分词: winding 第三人称单数: winds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('superb', '[suː\'pɜːrb]', 'adj.极好的', '1. The sports facilities are superb in this city. 这个城市的运动设施是一流的。 2. The goalkeeper brought off a superb save. 守门员漂亮地救出了险球。 3. Ideas will come to you easily and some will prove to be superb. 你总很容易就能想到好计划，其中一些将得到极好的证实。', '副词: superbly 名词: superbness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dialect', '[\'daɪəlekt]', 'n.方言；地方话', '1. Every now and then he would lapse into the local dialect. 他讲话中时而不自觉地冒出地方方言。 2. She speaks a dialect, not the Queen\'s English. 她说一口方言，不是标准英语。 3. The dialect is spoken principally in the rural areas. 这种方言主要在农村地区使用。 4. The use of dialect lent great charm to the work . 方言的运用给这部作品增添了巨大的魅力。', '形容词: dialectal 副词: dialectally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('start', '[stɑːrt]', 'v.开始；出发；震惊 n.开始；震动；领先优势；起推动作用的外力', '1. It started to rain. 下起雨来了. 2. I used to start work at 9 o\'clock every day. 我过去常在每天9：00开始工作。 3. We are just about to start. 我们正要出发。 4. She started at the sound of my voice. 她听到了我的声音，蓦地一惊。 5. He knew from the start the idea was hopeless. 一开始他就知道这主意行不通。', '过去式: started 过去分词: started 现在分词: starting 第三人称单数: starts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('governor', '[\'ɡʌvərnər]', 'n.统治者；管理者；理事；州长；总督；调节器', '1. The mob revolted against the governor. 暴民起来反抗统治者。 2. He established himself as governor of the province. 他当上了省长。 3. The governor decreed a day of mourning. 地方长官发布哀悼一日的命令。 4. It looks like the governor\'s personal guard. 看起来就像管理者的私人保卫者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deaf', '[def]', 'adj.聋的；充耳不闻的', '1. He is deaf in one ear. 他有一只耳朵是聋的。 2. He\'s a deaf mute and cannot tell anyone secret. 他是个聋哑人，不会把他们的秘密告诉任何人。 3. He is always deaf to his teacher\'s advice. 他总是对他老师的忠告充耳不闻。 4. He turns a deaf ear to criticism media. 他对媒体的批评充耳不闻。', '副词: deafly 比较级: deafer 最高级: deafest 名词: deafness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skeptical', '[\'skeptɪkəl]', 'adj.怀疑的', '1. He is skeptical about everything. 他对于一切事都持怀疑的态度。 2. Her tone is skeptical and detached. 她的声音是怀疑的，冷漠的。 3. The leader had the gift of being able to infuse enthusiasm into the most skeptical member of the group. 那位领导人很有天赋，能使团体中最持怀疑态度的人都充满热情。', '副词: skeptically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('offer', '[\'ɔːfər]', 'vt.提供；提出；（卖方）出价；贡献 vi.提议；出现；求婚 n.提议；出价', '1. We offer a free backup service to customers. 对顾客我们提供免费配套服务。 2. Can you offer any evidence in support of what you have said? 你能提出证据来印证你讲的话吗？ 3. We offered 100,000 for the warehouse, but another company outbid us. 我们出价1000,000英镑购买这个库房,但另一家公司出价高于我们。 4. China is a fascinating country. It has a lot to offer the world. 中国是个迷人的国家,她对世界的贡献是巨大的。 5. He offered to pay $1,000 for the second-hand car. 他提议付1,000美元买那辆二手车。 6. He will probably refuse the offer. 他很可能会拒绝这一提议。', '名词: offerer 过去式: offered 过去分词: offered 现在分词: offering 第三人称单数: offers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('receipt', '[rɪ\'siːt]', 'n.收据；收条；收到 v.出收据', '1. May I have a receipt? 我可以要一张收据吗？ 2. Please send me a receipt for the money. 请寄给我一张收到此款的收据。 3. We only take goods back if customers can produce the receipt. 顾客如能出示收据，我们才能予以退货。 4. Please give the receipt to the bearer. 收条请交来人带回。 5. His main work is to receipt for each lot of goods. 他的主要工作是给每一批货物开收据。', '过去式: receipted 过去分词: receipted 现在分词: receipting 第三人称单数: receipts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bankrupt', '[\'bæŋkrʌpt]', 'adj.破产的；道德败坏的；枯竭的 n.破产者；无知的人 vt.使破产', '1. If your liabilities exceed your assets, you may go bankrupt. 如果你所负的债超过你的资产，你就会破产。 2. I was bankrupt and unable to pay his debts. 我破产了，不能偿还他的债务。 3. He has been feeling low since he went bankrupt. 破产后他一直很消沉。 4. He believes that modern society is morally bankrupt. 他认为现代社会已丧失道德观念。 5. He realizes the bankrupt\'s assets. 他变卖破产者的财产。 6. Foolish expenditures will bankrupt him. 胡乱的花费将使他破产。', '形容词: bankruptive 名词: bankruptcy 过去式: bankrupted 过去分词: bankrupted 现在分词: bankrupting 第三人称单数: bankrupts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bee', '[biː]', 'n.蜜蜂 n.集会', '1. A bee pricks the skin with its sting. 蜜蜂用螫针刺皮肤。 2. He can hear the hum of the bee in the garden. 他听得见花园里蜜蜂的嗡嗡声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ceiling', '[\'siːlɪŋ]', 'n.天花板；上限', '1. He cracked his nut on the ceiling. 他的头让天花板碰破了。 2. The low ceiling of the room gave me a feeling of oppression. 低矮的屋顶给我一种压抑的感觉。 3. It took more or less a whole day to paint the ceiling. 粉刷天花板用了将近一整天的时间。 4. This ceiling has a carved panel. 这块天花板带有刻花镶板。', '形容词: ceilinged');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('strategy', '[\'strætədʒi]', 'n.策略；战略', '1. The strategy was designed to wear down the enemy\'s resistance. 这一策略旨在逐步削弱敌人的抵抗力。 2. We will discuss our sale strategy this year. 我们将讨论有关今年销售策略的问题。 3. He is an expert in military strategy. 他是军事战略专家。 4. Each country needs to forge its own industrial development strategy. 每个国家都需要制定自己的工业发展战略。', '名词复数: strategies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('revolutionary', '[ˌrevə\'luːʃəneri]', 'adj.革命的 n.革命者', '1. His heart glows with revolutionary enthusiasm. 他心中充满着革命的热情。 2. The revolutionary point remained primary. 革命的观点继续占上风。 3. He styles himself a revolutionary. 他自称为革命者。 4. A revolutionary\'s life used to be beset with dangers and hardships. 一个革命者的生活中往往充满危险和艰难。', '副词: revolutionarily 名词: revolutionariness 名词复数: revolutionaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('business', '[\'bɪznəs]', 'n.商业；事务；生意', '1. He had no head for business. 他毫无商业头脑。 2. He was inexperienced in business. 他在商业方面缺乏经验。 3. It\'s none of my business. 这不关我的事。 4. I don\'t understand this business. 我不了解这件事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('imagination', '[ɪˌmædʒɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.想象；想象力；空想；幻想', '1. That\'s beyond the reach of my imagination. 那是我想象不到的。 2. Imagination raises a man above the humdrum of life. 想象使人从单调无聊的生活中解脱出来。 3. These plans reveal a complete failure of imagination. 这些计划显得毫无想象力。 4. A sketch can stimulate one\'s own imagination. 图形能促进一个人的想象力。', '形容词: imaginational');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('goodby', '[ˌɡʊd\'baɪ]', 'int.再见 n.说再见', '1. Amid all the rush and confusion she forgot to say goodbye. 她在忙乱中忘记了告辞。 2. I\'d like to say goodbye to you all. 我想向你们大家告别了。 3. Amidst all the rush and confusion she forgot to say goodbye. 她在忙乱中忘记了告辞。 4. Goodbye till we meet again. 再见。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('battle', '[\'bætl]', 'n.战斗；争斗 v.与 ... 作战；与 ... 竞争', '1. His brave deeds in the battle earned him everlasting glory. 他在那场战斗中的英勇事迹为他赢得了永恒的荣誉。 2. He has proved his wit in the battle. 他已在这场争斗中证明了自己的睿智。 3. They battled with the wind and the waves. 他们与风浪搏斗。 4. Progress is slow but we keep battling on. 进展虽慢', '名词: battler 过去式: battled 过去分词: battled 现在分词: battling 第三人称单数: battles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('largely', '[\'lɑːrdʒli]', 'adv.大部分；主要地', '1. The farming area is centered largely in the south. 农业区大部分集中在南方。 2. His eight sons largely inherited his fortune. 他的八个儿子继承了他的大部分遗产。 3. We\'ll be dealing largely with the same themes, but from different angles. 我们将从不同的角度主要地研究这一课题。 4. However, in the East, there were many solar deities, including the Greek Helios, who was largely displaced by Apollo. 然而，在东方，有很多太阳神，包括希腊的太阳神，主要地是以阿波罗来命名。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('occupation', '[ˌɑːkju\'peɪʃn]', 'n.职业；占有；消遣；居住', '1. I haven\'t entered your name and occupation yet. 我尚未记下你的名字和职业。 2. Please state your name, age and occupation. 请说明姓名、年龄和职业。 3. He is a merchant in occupation. 他的职业是经商。 4. He returned from Paris and found his office was under someone else\'s occupation. 他从巴黎回来，发现他的办公室被别人占了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('act', '[ækt]', 'n.行为；行动；法案；(戏剧、歌剧等的)一幕；假装 v.行动；举止；假装；表演；扮演；充当；有效果', '1. It is an act of kindness to help a blind man across the street. 帮助盲人过街是慈善的行为。 2. This act had to get a strong support from them. 这个行动必须得到他们的大力支持。 3. In 1601, Parliament passed an act, which aimed to provide the poor with more jobs. 1601年,国会通过了一项旨在向贫困群体提供更多工作机会的法案。 4. Don\'t take her seriously--it\'s all an act. 别跟她认真--完全是装腔作势。 5. Think well before you act. 要三思而后行。', '形容词: actable 名词: actability 过去式: acted 过去分词: acted 现在分词: acting 第三人称单数: acts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('drift', '[drɪft]', 'vi.漂流；漂移；吹积；漂泊；偏离 vt.使漂流；使堆积 n.漂流；趋势；漂泊', '1. The sailors cast the boat off and allowed it to drift away on the tide. 水手解下缆绳，任船随潮流漂走。 2. The boat drifted down the river. 船顺水漂流而下。 3. What causes continents to break up and drift apart? 什么原因导致大陆分裂漂移? 4. Some roads are closed owing to drifting. 有些道路因积雪而封闭。 5. They drift the logs down the river to the sawmills. 他们使那些圆木漂下河流到锯木厂。 6. The general drift of the current was northerly. 这水通常向北流。', '形容词: drifty 过去式: drifted 过去分词: drifted 现在分词: drifting 第三人称单数: drifts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gesture', '[\'dʒestʃər]', 'n.手势；姿势 v.作手势表达', '1. Japanese don\'t use as much gesture as Europeans. 日本人使用手势没有欧美人那样多。 2. The children were diverted with his funny gesture. 他那滑稽的手势使孩子们很开心。 3. He put his arm round her in a protective gesture. 他用一只手臂围住她做出保护的姿势。 4. He raised his hands in a gesture of despair. 他举起双手做出绝望的姿势。 5. The doctor gestured me to take off my coat. 医生做手势要我脱去外套。', '形容词: gestural 副词: gesturally 名词: gesturer 过去式: gestured 过去分词: gestured 现在分词: gesturing 第三人称单数: gestures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('splendid', '[\'splendɪd]', 'adj.极好的；辉煌的；壮观的；杰出的', '1. Playing tabletennis is a splendid sport. 打乒乓球是极好的运动。 2. My kid sister has a splendid memory. 我小妹记忆力极好。 3. We won another splendid victory. 我们又赢得了辉煌的胜利。 4. The royal couple appeared in splendid array. 王室伉俪身穿盛装出现。', '副词: splendidly 名词: splendidness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skim', '[skɪm]', 'vt.撇去；略读；掠过；滑过 vi.掠过；表面凝结；<俚>瞒报 n.浮沫；略读；脱脂物', '1. It took me an hour to skim the book. 我花了一小时把这本书浏览了一遍。 2. A seagull skims the water. 海鸥掠过水面。 3. The hovercraft is able to skim over the water. 气垫船能掠过水面飞速行驶。 4. During the cold night, the puddles skimmed over. 夜间寒冷，水洼面上结了冰。 5. I notice you have two quarts of skim milk. 我看到你拿了两夸托脱脂牛奶。', '过去式: skimmed 过去分词: skimmed 现在分词: skimming 第三人称单数: skims');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lately', '[\'leɪtli]', 'adv.最近', '1. I haven\'t had enough sleep lately. 最近我睡眠不足。 2. I\'ve not been feeling very well lately. 我最近一直感觉不太好。 3. I haven\'t heard any news from my son lately. 我最近没听到我儿子的任何音讯。 4. Frank has taken up with Lucy lately. 弗兰克最近经常与露西往来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('projector', '[prə\'dʒektər]', 'n.放映机；探照灯；计划者；投影线', '1. How long will it take to set up the projector? 把这个放映机安放好需要多长时间? 2. The film flew off the spool and wound itself round the projector. 电影胶片从卷轴滑出缠绕在放映机上了。 3. I do not deny that the projector is top quality. 我并不否认放映机质量上乘。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('regret', '[rɪ\'ɡret]', 'v.后悔；惋惜；为 ... 感到遗憾 n.遗憾；抱歉；后悔', '1. I now regret having made a promise that I would join in the scheme. 我现在后悔答应参加该计划的事。 2. We deeply regret that this big fire has taken away two young men\'s lives. 这次大火夺走了两个年轻人的生命,我们为此感到深深的惋惜。 3. We regret that we have to place the entire shipment at your disposal. 很遗憾，我们只得将全部货品退回贵方自行处理。 4. My only regret is that I have missed the chance to go abroad for further education. 我唯一遗憾的是错过了去国外进修的机会。', '名词: regretter 过去式: regretted 过去分词: regretted 现在分词: regretting 第三人称单数: regrets');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('next', '[nekst]', 'adj.下一个的；其次的；隔壁的 adv.其次；下次；然后 n.下一个 prep.靠近', '1. If I miss this train I\'ll catch the next one. 如果我错过了这班火车，就赶乘下一班。 2. Let\'s pass on to the next item on the agenda. 咱们进行议事日程的下一个项目吧。 3. The next best thing would be to tell him the truth. 其次，最好的办法就是把真相告诉他们。 4. She\'s in the room next door to her parents. 她住在她父母隔壁的那个房间。 5. Next, there was the matter of her clothes. 其次，还有她的服装问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('teenager', '[\'tiːneɪdʒər]', 'n.青少年；13岁到19岁的年轻人', '1. He is a lanky teenager. 他是个瘦削的少年。 2. It is not easy to educate teenagers. 教育青少年不是件容易的事。 3. That teenager singer is really dynamite! 那个少年歌手真是轰动一时！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stitch', '[stɪtʃ]', 'n.一针；疼痛；碎布条 v.缝合', '1. Every stitch was in its right place. 每一针的位置都很贴切。 2. When she sews she makes long stitches. 她做针线活时针脚很大。 3. He felt a sort of stitch in his heart. 他感到有点心痛。 4. The doctor can stitch up the wound skillfully. 这位医生缝合伤口技术甚高。', '名词: stitcher 过去式: stitched 过去分词: stitched 现在分词: stitching 第三人称单数: stitches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('remainder', '[rɪ\'meɪndər]', 'n.剩余物；其余的人；[数]余数 vt.廉价出售', '1. The remainder must be paid by the end of June. 剩余部分的金额必须在月底前付清。 2. He spent the remainder of his life in the country. 他在乡村度过余生。 3. Nine people came in and the remainder stayed outside. 9个人进来，余下的人留在外面。 4. Take 4 from 9 and the remainder is 5. 9除以4余数为5。', '过去式: remaindered 过去分词: remaindered 现在分词: remaindering 第三人称单数: remainders');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('witch', '[wɪtʃ]', 'n.女巫；巫婆 vt.施巫术 vi.用神杖发现地下水源或矿物', '1. The wedding was in full swing when the witch came in. 当女巫进来时婚礼正进行得热闹。 2. The witch put the princess under a spell, and she fell asleep for ten years. 这女巫使公主中了巫术，沉睡了十年。 3. The witch charmed the prince. 女巫对王子施了魔法。 4. The witch turned the princess into a swan. 巫婆把公主变成了一只天鹅。 5. The little princess was withced. 小公主被施了巫术。', '形容词: witchy 名词: witchery 过去式: witched 过去分词: witched 现在分词: witching 第三人称单数: witches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('faint', '[feɪnt]', 'adj.微弱的；无力的；模糊的 v.昏倒 n.昏厥；昏倒', '1. A faint hope still flickered in her breast. 一种微弱的希望仍在她的心中闪动着。 2. He could discern a faint light ahead in the forest. 他能看到前面森林里有一线微弱的灯光。 3. I heard a faint sound in the distance. 我听到远处有个微弱的声音。 4. Every time I think of it I feel faint! 每次想到这些 5. You\'d better attend to that girl. I think she\'s going to faint. 你最好去照顾那女孩，我看她快昏倒了。 6. The little girl went off in a faint,but the doctor pulled her round very soon. 小女孩昏倒了，但医生很快使她苏醒过来。', '副词: faintly 比较级: fainter 最高级: faintest 名词: fainter 过去式: fainted 过去分词: fainted 现在分词: fainting 第三人称单数: faints');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tease', '[tiːz]', 'n.揶揄者；戏弄 v.欺负；嘲弄', '1. He is a terrible tease. 他特别爱戏弄人。 2. It\'s too bad of you to tease the child like that. 你那样逗弄小孩真不好。 3. You must never tease a child because he stutters . 你切不可因为一个孩子口吃而去取笑他。 4. Don\'t take it seriously. He\'s only teasing. 别把它当真，他只不过是在开玩笑。', '副词: teasingly 过去式: teased 过去分词: teased 现在分词: teasing 第三人称单数: teases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pepper', '[\'pepər]', 'n.胡椒粉；辣椒 vt.加胡椒粉于；不断打击', '1. The pepper in the food caused me to sneeze. 这食物中的胡椒味儿呛得我直打喷嚏。 2. This kind of green pepper is very hot. 这种青辣椒非常辣。 3. You don\'t have to pepper the soup. 你不一定要往汤里撒胡椒粉。 4. The wall had been peppered with bullets. 墙上有密集的子弹痕迹。', '过去式: peppered 过去分词: peppered 现在分词: peppering 第三人称单数: peppers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deer', '[dɪr]', 'n.鹿，梅花鹿', '1. The deer darted away at the sight of a lion. 鹿一见狮子就飞奔而逃。 2. There were deer in abundance in these forests. 这些森林中有许多鹿。', '名词复数: deer');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bargain', '[\'bɑːrɡən]', 'n.交易；便宜货；契约 v.讨价还价；议价；(谈价钱后)卖', '1. He made a satisfactory bargain with them. 他和他们做了一笔满意的交易。 2. If you promote our goods, we will give you a good discount as our part of the bargain. 若你方经销我们的货物，我方愿给予你相当大的优惠作为回报。 3. She knows a bargain when she sees one. 她有辨别便宜货的能力。 4. There never was a better bargain driver. 再没有比这更美好的契约。 5. The salesman refused to bargain over the price. 推销员拒绝讨价还价。', '名词: bargainer 过去式: bargained 过去分词: bargained 现在分词: bargaining 第三人称单数: bargains');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obstacle', '[\'ɑːbstəkl]', 'n.障碍；绊脚石', '1. Lack of education is an obstacle of success. 缺乏教育是成功的障碍。 2. This is the chief obstacle to world peace. 这是世界和平的主要障碍。 3. He took every obstacle in his stride. 他轻易地度过一切难关。 4. Overstaffing has become the obstacle for reforms. 人浮于事已成为改革的绊脚石。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('over', '[\'oʊvər]', 'prep.在 ... 的上方；遍及地；在 ... 期间 adv.穿过；完全覆盖；结束；落下 n.(板球中)每个投球手一次连续所投出的球数', '1. The lamp hung over the table. 那盏灯悬挂在桌子上方。 2. He sprinkled sugar over his cereal. 他在麦片粥里撒上了糖。 3. He scattered his clothes all over the floor. 他把衣服扔了一地。 4. He went to sleep over his work. 他干着干着活儿就睡著了。 5. We must go over the mountain. 我们必须越过那座山。', '过去式: overed 过去分词: overed 现在分词: overing 第三人称单数: overs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('percent', '[pə\'sent]', 'n.百分比 adv.百分之 ... adj.百分之 ... 的', '1. The number of queues repaired out of the percent detected. 修复的队列数目超过检测到的百分比。 2. Twenty percent of the products are exported. 百分之二十的产品外销。 3. The company\'s market share is 48 percent in the marketplace. 这家公司的市场占有率是百分之四十八。 4. The gross national product had increased 5 percent last year. 去年的国民生产总值提高了百分之五。 5. I am a hundred percent in agreement with you. 我百分之百同意你的看法。 6. We give 10 percent discount for cash. 现金付款，我们九折优惠。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('brake', '[breɪk]', 'n.制动器；闸；刹车 v.刹车', '1. There\'s too much travel on the brake, it needs tightening. 制动器太松了，需要调紧。 2. After the work, remember to shut off the brake and remain neatness. 使用后必须拉闸,要保持卫生。 3. The brake doesn\'t grip properly. 刹车不灵了。 4. A lot of the cost of maintenance go into renew brake. 很多的维修费用都花在了更换煞车方面。 5. The car in front of me stopped suddenly and I had to brake. 我前面那辆小汽车突然停住，我只好刹车。', '过去式: braked 过去分词: braked 现在分词: braking 第三人称单数: brakes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('central', '[\'sentrəl]', 'adj.中心的；中央的；主要的；起支配作用的；有控制力的；[语]中央元音的 n.中心枢纽；中央办公室；电话交换机', '1. My house is very central. 我的家非常靠近市中心。 2. What\'s the central thought of this article? 这篇文章的中心思想是什么？ 3. She stays in a small hotel near central park. 她住在中央公园附近的一家小旅馆。 4. She has been a central figure in the campaign. 她一直是这场运动的主要人物。', '副词: centrally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Christian', '[\'krɪstʃən]', 'n.基督徒 adj.基督教的；基督徒的', '1. He is a pious Christian. 他是一名虔诚的基督教徒。 2. My husband is a Christian and I’m going to turn. 我丈夫是基督徒，我也准备皈依基督教。 3. The man was excommunicated from the Christian Church. 那人被驱逐出基督教会。 4. Christian and Muslim doctrines are very different. 基督教教义和穆斯林教义极为不同。', '形容词: Christianly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('regarding', '[rɪ\'ɡɑːrdɪŋ]', 'prep.关于；至于', '1. She said nothing regarding your request. 她对你的要求只字不提。 2. I wrote a letter regarding my daughter\'s school examinations. 我写了一封关于我女儿学校考试的信。 3. The map is in error regarding the junction. 这张地图在这个交点上是绘制错了。 4. I care about nothing regarding my future career. 至于未来,我一点儿也不关心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sigh', '[saɪ]', 'n.叹气；叹息 v.叹息；惋惜', '1. When he heard the news, he uttered a sigh. 听到这消息时，他叹了口气。 2. She heaved a sigh and became lost in thought. 她叹了口气，随即陷入了沉思。 3. The old man uttered a sigh and went out. 那位老人叹息了一声,走了出去。 4. I bury my face in my hands and heave a sigh. 我掩着面叹息。 5. He sighed with despair. 他绝望地叹了口气。', '名词: sigher 过去式: sighed 过去分词: sighed 现在分词: sighing 第三人称单数: sighs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('downstairs', '[ˌdaʊn\'sterz]', 'adj.楼下的 adv.在楼下；向楼下 n.楼下', '1. Your downstairs neighbor let me in. 楼下的邻居让我进来的。 2. The young man downstairs is a lawyer. 楼下的那位年轻人是律师。 3. The children made a loud noise downstairs. 孩子们在楼下大声喧哗。 4. He sat sipping grog alone downstairs. 他坐在楼下慢慢地把水酒独酌。 5. I\'ll remodel the downstairs bedroom first. 我先要装修楼下那间房间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('obsession', '[əb\'seʃn]', 'n.困扰；沉迷；着魔；妄想', '1. Winning is no longer just a goal;it becomes an obsession. 打赢官司不再仅仅是一个目标，更成为一种无法摆脱的困扰。 2. I was suffering from obsession that my career would be ended. 那时的我陷入了我的事业有可能就此终止的困扰当中。 3. Her obsession with mah-jongg began three months ago. 她对麻将的沉迷是三个月前开始的。 4. \"This isn\'t just a whim of mine, it\'s a magnificent obsession! 跑步并不是我的一时冲动,而是一种疯狂的着迷！', '形容词: obsessional 副词: obsessionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('share', '[ʃer]', 'vt.分享，共享；分配；共有 vi.分享 n.一份；股份；分担；犁头', '1. Children should be taught to share their toys. 应该教育孩子们分享玩具。 2. Keep your fears to yourself but share your courage with others. 把恐惧留给自己,和他人分享勇气。 3. Share the fruit among your friends. 把水果分给你的朋友们。 4. I share a bedroom with my sister. 我和我姐姐合住一间卧室。 5. There is only one bedroom, so we\'ll have to share 只有一间卧室,所以我们得合着用。 6. Your share of the cost is 10 pounds. 你这一份费用是10英镑。', '形容词: shareable 名词: sharer 过去式: shared 过去分词: shared 现在分词: sharing 第三人称单数: shares');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spectacle', '[\'spektəkl]', 'n.景象；场面；奇观；壮观；公开展示；表相，假相 n.（复）眼镜', '1. The sunrise was a splendid spectacle. 日出是个壮观的景象。 2. The celebrations provided a magnificent spectacle. 庆祝活动呈现一派宏伟的景象。 3. The carnival parade was a magnificent spectacle. 狂欢节游行场面热烈，蔚为大观。 4. The children took in the spectacle open-mouthed. 孩子们张着嘴注视精彩表演。 5. I can\'t see things through your spectacles. 我和你的看法不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('equal', '[\'iːkwəl]', 'adj.相等的；平等的 vt.比得上；等于 n.同辈；平等；(同等的)人或事物', '1. Women demand equal pay for equal work. 妇女要求同工同酬。 2. All countries, big and small, should be equal. 国家不论大小, 一律平等。 3. Nobody can equal him in intelligence. 没有人在智力方面能比得上他。 4. Three and five equals eight. 三加五等于八。 5. They are my equals in age. 我和他们是同龄人。', '副词: equally 过去式: equaled/equalled 过去分词: equaled/equalled 现在分词: equaling/equalling 第三人称单数: equals/equals');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ounce', '[aʊns]', 'n.盎司', '1. An ounce of action is worth a ton of theory. 一盎司的行动就能值一吨的理论。 2. So, one is your alcohol, one ounce vodka. 所以，一是酒，一盎司伏特加。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('return', '[rɪ\'tɜːrn]', 'v.返回；归还；回报；回应；申报 n.归还；返回；（收益)回报；申报', '1. We must return to Dalian within three days. 我们必须在3日内回到大连。 2. What time does your husband return from work? 你丈夫什么时候下班回家？ 3. Don\'t forget to return my keys. 别忘了还我钥匙。 4. Good education is an investment for your future and will return substantial rewards. 接受优质教育是对自己未来的投资并会获得高回报投资。 5. I\'m afraid I have to insist on the return of my books at once. 对不起,我要求你立即归还我的书。', '名词: returner 过去式: returned 过去分词: returned 现在分词: returning 第三人称单数: returns');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wardrobe', '[\'wɔːrdroʊb]', 'n.衣橱，衣柜；全部服装', '1. The wardrobe takes up too much space. 这衣橱太占地方了。 2. All the shirts hang together in the same wardrobe. 所有的衬衫都挂在同一个衣橱里。 3. Such an outfit would be a useful addition to my wardrobe. 在我的服装中添置这一套会有用的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('angel', '[\'eɪndʒl]', 'n.天使；天使般的人', '1. A stunt man needs to have a good guardian angel. 当特技替身演员的得有个守护天使来保佑。 2. No sin at all is the dream of the angel. 不犯错误，那是天使的梦想。 3. She is painting an angel with outspread wings. 她正在画一个张开翅膀的天使。 4. She is lovely -- as much so as an angel. 她可爱得像个天使。', '形容词: angelic 副词: angelically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('defy', '[dɪ\'faɪ]', 'vt.藐视；挑衅；反抗', '1. The pine trees defy severe cold. 松树不畏严寒。 2. If you defy the law, you will be sent to prison. 如果你蔑视法律，你将被送入监狱。 3. He defined the order of the court. 他蔑视法庭的命令。 4. He won\'t allow anyone to defy his ministerial authority. 他不允许任何人挑衅他的教长权威。', '过去式: defied 过去分词: defied 现在分词: defying 第三人称单数: defies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plug', '[plʌɡ]', 'n.塞子；插头；推销；火花塞；口嚼烟 v.塞；堵；宣传；插上插头；苦干', '1. She pulled the plug out of the bathtub and the dirty water ran away. 她把浴缸的塞子拔掉，脏水流走了。 2. She put the electric plug into the socket. 她将电插头插到了插座里。 3. The TV compere gave her new record a plug. 电视节目主持人极力推荐她的新唱片。 4. Fuel is ignited by the spark plug. 燃料由火花塞点火。 5. You don\'t need to plug your ears. The music is not so loud. 你不用塞住耳朵,音乐又不是很吵。', '名词: plugger 过去式: plugged 过去分词: plugged 现在分词: plugging 第三人称单数: plugs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quantify', '[\'kwɑːntɪfaɪ]', 'v.用数量表示；量化', '1. The cost of the flood damage is impossible to quantify. 这次水灾的损失是无可估量的。 2. Now, a new study has helped quantify this trend. 现在有一项新的研究对这一趋势进行了量化。 3. It\'s difficult to quantify the value of space exploration. 把太空探索的价值进行量化是很困难的。', '形容词: quantifiable 名词: quantification 过去式: quantified 过去分词: quantified 现在分词: quantifying 第三人称单数: quantifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('feed', '[fiːd]', 'vt.喂养；饲养；靠 ... 为生；向 ... 提供 vi.吃饲料；进餐 n.一餐；饲料；饲养', '1. Will you feed my cat for me? 请帮我喂我的猫好吗？ 2. What do you feed the poultry on? 你们用什么饲料喂养家禽? 3. They feed on plankton, the sea\'s drifting life. 它们吃以浮游生物为生。 4. Dor locate flying insects on which they feed. 或者找到它们赖以为生的昆虫。 5. Birds feed on worms and grains. 鸟以虫和谷物为食。 6. How many feeds a day does this dog get? 这只狗每天吃几顿？', '过去式: fed 过去分词: fed 现在分词: feeding 第三人称单数: feeds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('role', '[roʊl]', 'n.作用；角色', '1. The Panama Canal has played a very important role in transportation. 巴拿马运河在运输上起到了非常重要的作用。 2. The key role of the teacher in the learning process should not be neglected. 教师在学习中的关键作用是不该忽视的。 3. The role of the railway declines in the transport system. 在运输系统中,铁路的重要性逐渐下降。 4. She prefers to play comic roles. 她更喜欢扮演滑稽角色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hinge', '[hɪndʒ]', 'n.铰链；关键 vt.用铰链装 vi.依情况而定', '1. The two bones are articulated like a hinge. 这两块骨头由关节铰链般连接起来。 2. Rust is eating away the iron hinge. 铁锈正腐蚀着铁铰链。 3. This was the hinge of fate of the whole campaign. 这是决定整场战役命运的关键点。 4. Your arm should hinge from the shoulder. 你的手臂应该像从肩膀铰链住一般。 5. His acceptance will hinge upon the term. 他接受与否将依条件而定。', '过去式: hinged 过去分词: hinged 现在分词: hinging 第三人称单数: hinges');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('deny', '[dɪ\'naɪ]', 'vt.否认；拒绝承认；拒绝给予；自制', '1. He is not trustworthy, but at the same time, we cannot deny that he is clever. 他不可信赖,然而我们不能否认他很聪明。 2. He denied that it was his fault. 他拒不承认这是他的过错。 3. I was denied the chance of going to university. 我得不到上大学的机会。 4. We should try to deny ourselves from indulging in computer games. 我们应该尽力克制自己,不使自己沉溺于电脑游戏。', '过去式: denied 过去分词: denied 现在分词: denying 第三人称单数: denies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('southern', '[\'sʌðərn]', 'adj.南部的；南方的', '1. He lives in southern China. 他住在中国南部。 2. Only in the southern part of Taiwan have I seen such scenery as this. 唯有在南台湾我才见过像这样的风景。 3. The secession of some southern states from the USA in the 1860s led to the civil war. 由于南部某些州于十九世纪六十年代脱离美国而导致了南北战争。 4. Rice is the chief crop in most southern provinces. 稻子是大多数南方省份的主要作物。', '名词: southernness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nervous', '[\'nɜːrvəs]', 'adj.神经的，神经细胞的，神经性的；焦虑的；神经质的，紧张的，不安的；易兴奋的', '1. The doctors shall operate on his central nervous system. 医生们将要对他的中枢神经系统动手术。 2. He is suffering from nervous tension. 他正受神经紧张之苦。 3. They can also help come calm and control nervous horses and got cheap guard sheep and gots goats on farms. 它们也可以使紧张焦虑的马平静下来，它们同样可以保卫绵羊和山羊。 4. The merest little thing makes him nervous. 最微不足道的小事也会使他紧张。', '副词: nervously 名词: nervousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('roll', '[roʊl]', 'n.卷；滚动；名单；压路机；颤音；圆形物，面包卷 v.摇摆；滚；绕；转动；展开', '1. Love comes quick and passes away quick too. Only the pork roll will go on. 爱情来得快去得也快,只有猪肉卷才是永恒的。 2. The desk calculator use a roll of paper. 这台台式计算机使用卷纸。 3. A ball can roll smoothly on a plane. 球可以在水平面上流畅地滚动。 4. Merlin tried different ways to make himself roll. 莫林试了很多不同的方式，想让自己滚动起来。 5. The ship was rolling heavily to and fro. 那船晃来晃去很不平稳。', '过去式: rolled 过去分词: rolled 现在分词: rolling 第三人称单数: rolls');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cheque', '[tʃek]', 'n.支票 =check(美).', '1. Don\'t forget to date your cheque. 不要忘记在支票上写上日期。 2. I hope this cheque doesn\'t bounce. 我希望这张支票别遭退票 3. He drew a cheque to her. 他开了张支票给她。 4. Payments by cheque easily outnumbered cash transactions. 用支票付款在数量上大大超过现金交易。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hold', '[hoʊld]', 'v.拿着；控制；容纳；握住；持有；保持；掌握；认为；举行 n.握住；控制；把握；立足点；延误；影响', '1. I want you to stand beside me and hold the torch. 我要你拿着手电筒站在我旁边。 2. He has been trying hard to hold his temper. 他一直尽力控制自己不发脾气。 3. The new football stadium can hold eighty thousand people. 新的足球场可以容纳八万人。 4. I\'ll always be the one to firmly hold your hands. 我永远都会坚定地握住你的手。 5. His hold on her arm tightened. 他把她的胳膊抓得更紧了。', '过去式: held 过去分词: held 现在分词: holding 第三人称单数: holds');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abstract', '[\'æbstrækt]', 'adj.抽象的；理论的；抽象派的 n.摘要；抽象派艺术作品 v.(/æbˈstrækt/)把…抽象出；提取；抽取；转移(注意力等)；做…的摘要；<婉>偷', '1. We may talk of beautiful things, but beauty itself is abstract. 我们尽可谈论美的事物，然而美本身却是抽象的。 2. He has some abstract notion of wanting to change the world. 他有一种要改造世界的空想。 3. Abstract paintings did not appeal to him. 抽象派绘画引不起他的兴趣。 4. The whole text of the abstract shall contain not more than 300 Chinese characters. 摘要文字部分不得超过300个字。 5. She abstracted the main points from the argument. 她把论据概括成要点。', '副词: abstractly 名词: abstracter 过去式: abstracted 过去分词: abstracted 现在分词: abstracting 第三人称单数: abstracts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('protest', '[\'proʊtest]', 'n.抗议；反对 v.抗议；反对；申明；断言', '1. Half a million people held a mass protest against racism last night. 昨晚50万人举行了大规模的抗议活动反对种族歧视。 2. Some delegates walked out in a show of protest. 有几位代表退出会场以示抗议。 3. The minister resigned in protest against the decision. 这位部长为反对那项决策而辞职。 4. They protested to the mayor that the taxes were too high. 他们向市长提出抗议说税款过高。', '副词: protestingly 名词: protester 过去式: protested 过去分词: protested 现在分词: protesting 第三人称单数: protests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('complication', '[ˌkɑːmplɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.复杂；并发症；纠纷', '1. This was an unforeseen complication. 这是未预见到的复杂情况。 2. We cannot allow further complication of this matter. 我们不能让这件事变得更复杂了。 3. Complications set in, and the patient died. 病人因出现并发症而死亡。 4. Pneumonia is the complication we most fear. 肺炎是我们最害怕的并发症。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('crime', '[kraɪm]', 'n.犯罪；恶行', '1. He was acquitted of the crime. 他被宣告无罪。 2. His addiction to drugs propelled him towards a life of crime. 他吸毒成瘾使他走上了犯罪的道路。 3. The government is alarmed by the dramatic increase in violent crime. 政府对暴力犯罪案件的急剧增加感到担心。 4. It\'s a crime the way he bullies his children. 像他那样欺负自己的孩子真缺德。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enterprise', '[\'entərpraɪz]', 'n.企业；事业；进取心；谋划', '1. This enterprise is now on a firm footing and should soon get profits. 现在这家企业基础稳固，很快就会赢利。 2. They are involved in an exciting scientific enterprise. 他们投身于一项激动人心的科学事业。 3. We need a spirit of enterprise if we are to overcome our difficulties. 如果我们要克服困难，我们就要有进取精神。 4. His latest business enterprise has attracted a lot of attention. 他最新的企业规划引来了很多关注。', '名词: enterpriser');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prosperous', '[\'prɑːspərəs]', 'adj.繁荣的；兴旺的', '1. At no time has the country been more prosperous than at present. 我国任何时候都没有现在这样繁荣。 2. There are some areas of poverty, but the country as a whole is fairly prosperous. 这个国家有些地区比较贫困, 但总的来说是相当富裕的。 3. The city at one time must have been prosperous, for It enjoyed a high level of civilization. 这座古城在一个时期准是很繁荣的，因为它曾享有高度文明。 4. His business is prosperous. 他的事业兴旺发达。', '副词: prosperously 名词: prosperousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fail', '[feɪl]', 'vi.失败；没做成某事；表现欠佳；用完；衰退 vt.辜负；放弃；缺少；不及格 n.不及格；没做成', '1. We must hang together,or our plan will fail. 我们必须齐心协力,否则我们的计划就会失败。 2. He never fails to write to his mother every week. 他从来没有忘记每周给母亲写信。 3. He studied hard only to fail in the exam. 他这么用功，结果竟然考场失利。 4. The water supply failed during the drought. 在干旱期供水不足 5. Your performance failed your coach who thought that you could have done better. 你的表现辜负了教练的期望,他认为你本可以做得更好一些。 6. He got a fail in history and passes in other subjects. 他历史考试不及格，其他科目都通过了。', '过去式: failed 过去分词: failed 现在分词: failing 第三人称单数: fails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('justify', '[\'dʒʌstɪfaɪ]', 'vt.替 ... 辩护；证明 ... 正当；调整版面', '1. He had to justify himself for his conduct. 他不得不为自己的行为辩白。 2. Don\'t try to justify your mistakes. 不要为自己的缺点辩护。 3. Nothing can justify your cheating on an exam. 任何事情都不能成为你考试作弊的理由。 4. Such action can be justified on the grounds of greater efficiency. 以提高功效为依据可以证明采取这种措施是正确的。', '过去式: justified 过去分词: justified 现在分词: justifying 第三人称单数: justifies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sip', '[sɪp]', 'n.啜饮 v.啜饮；啜', '1. He took one sip of the wine and spat it out. 他抿了一口酒，又吐了出来。 2. He paused to take a sip of water, and then went on with his story. 他停下来呷了一口水，然後继续讲他的事。 3. I sipped at the coffee. 我啜饮咖啡。 4. When you drink your soup, don\'t sip it, but swallow it all in one mouthful. 喝汤时不要啜饮,而应一口吞下去。', '名词: sipper 过去式: sipped 过去分词: sipped 现在分词: sipping 第三人称单数: sips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tower', '[\'taʊər]', 'n.塔；高楼 vi.高耸；胜过', '1. There is a sonorous bell in the tower. 塔里有一口洪亮的钟。 2. The tower was blown to atoms by the force of the explosion. 爆炸的力量把塔炸得粉碎。 3. The bell tower is the emblem of this city. 这座钟楼是这个城市的象征。 4. Above the victorian houses and shops tower the monster office blocks of the redeveloped center. 高耸于维多利亚时代房屋店铺之上的是新开发的市中心高大的办公楼群。', '过去式: towered 过去分词: towered 现在分词: towering 第三人称单数: towers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('unity', '[\'juːnəti]', 'n.整体；统一；一致；结合', '1. These works, taken together, are essentially a unity. 这些作品，放在一起，基本上是一个整体。 2. The figure on the left spoils the unity of the painting. 左边的人物有损于画面的整体性。 3. He made a speech about the need for unity. 他发表了有关统一之必要的演讲。 4. They maintained only formal unity among themselves. 他们只在表面上保持一致。', '名词复数: unities');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('measure', '[\'meʒər]', 'n.措施；量度；尺寸；程度；办法 v.测量；比较；给予；权衡', '1. The government has taken measures to restrain inflation. 政府已采取措施控制通货膨胀。 2. The standard kilogram is maintained as a measure of mass. 标准的千克是测量质量的量度 3. I want the suit made to his own measure. 我想要这套西装照他自己的尺寸做。 4. You are right in some measure. 从某种程度上来说你是对的。 5. They measured the height of the ceiling. 他们测量了天花板的高度。', '名词: measurer 过去式: measured 过去分词: measured 现在分词: measuring 第三人称单数: measures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('twinkle', '[\'twɪŋkl]', 'vi.闪耀；闪烁；眨眼；轻快移动 vt.使闪耀 n.闪烁；闪耀；眨眼；瞬息', '1. We could see lights twinkling in the little town below. 我们可以看见下面的小镇灯光闪耀。 2. He stared up at the stars twinkling in the sky above him. 他抬眼凝视着头顶上方星光闪烁的天空。 3. The dancer\'s feet twinkled. 舞蹈演员的脚在轻快地移动。 4. The star seemed to twinkle hope to us. 这颗星星似乎向我们闪烁希望。 5. From the twinkle in her eyes I knew she was joking. 我从她眼中的闪烁得知她在开玩笑。', '形容词: twinkly 名词: twinkler 过去式: twinkled 过去分词: twinkled 现在分词: twinkling 第三人称单数: twinkles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('assurance', '[ə\'ʃʊrəns]', 'n.保证，担保；确信；自信；保险', '1. He gave me assurance in black and white. 他给了我书面保证。 2. I have full assurance of his honesty. 我完全相信他的诚实。 3. He gave me a definite assurance that the repairs would be finished tomorrow. 他给我确切保证，修理将于明日完工。 4. They were waiting with assurance for me to discover the truth for myself. 他们自信地等待我自己发现事实真相。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('expire', '[ɪk\'spaɪər]', 'vi.终止；期满；失效；呼气；断气', '1. Our holidays expire next week. 我们的假期于下星期结束。 2. My passport is due to expire in two months. 我的护照再过两个月就到期了。 3. When does your driving licence expire? 你的驾驶执照何时到期? 4. My credit card will expire in June. 我的信用卡六月过期。', '过去式: expired 过去分词: expired 现在分词: expiring 第三人称单数: expires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('collide', '[kə\'laɪd]', 'vi.碰撞；互撞；砥触', '1. The bus and the van collided. 公共汽车与客货车相撞。 2. The ships collided in the fog. 轮船在雾中相撞。 3. As the bus turned the corner, it collided with a van. 公共汽车转过拐角时与客货车相撞。 4. But during the collision, one galaxy can rip the other apart gravitationally, and dust and gas common to both galaxies does collide. 当星系互撞期间，星系可能因重力拉扯另外一个星系，尘埃与云气也会因此而合并。', '过去式: collided 过去分词: collided 现在分词: colliding 第三人称单数: collides');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('society', '[sə\'saɪəti]', 'n.社会；(共同遵守一定的习俗、法律等的）特定群体；社团；协会；上层社会；社交圈；交往', '1. This event had a pernicious influence on society. 这件事情对社会造成了有害的影响。 2. The whole fabric of the society was changed by the war. 战争改变了整个社会结构。 3. Credit is the life-blood of the consumer society. 信誉是消费界的生命线。 4. Can Britain ever be a classless society? 英国能否有朝一日成为一个无阶级社会?', '名词复数: societies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('delicate', '[\'delɪkət]', 'adj.微妙的；精美的；纤细的；脆弱的；敏锐的；美味的', '1. The international situation is very delicate at present. 目前的国际形势极其微妙。 2. He persecuted me with various delicate questions. 他用种种微妙的问题把我难倒了。 3. She wears a dress with delicate lace. 她穿了一件带有精致花边的裙子。 4. Don\'t grasp at the delicate branch, or you may break it. 不要去抓这嫩枝,你会把它折断的。', '副词: delicately 名词: delicateness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('primary', '[\'praɪmeri]', 'adj.首要的；主要的；初级的；初等教育的；根本的；初期的 n.第一位；初选；最主要者；要素；原色；初级线圈', '1. The primary task for socialism is to develop the productive forces. 社会主义的首要任务是发展社会生产力。 2. Another primary reason is that there seems to be too many private cars and not enough public buses. 另一个主要原因是私家车过多而公交车不够。 3. The demand for primary products is on the increase in European market. 欧洲市场对初级产品的需求在增长。 4. Primary education comes under the umbrella of local government. 小学教育受地方政府的保护。 5. We should place development on the primary in governing and rejuvenating the country. 我们应将发展放在执政兴国中的第一位。', '名词复数: primaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('allowance', '[ə\'laʊəns]', 'n.零用钱；津贴；限额，定量；允许；折扣；考虑', '1. I didn\'t receive any allowance from my father. 我没有收到父亲给的零用钱。 2. I have to work to earn my allowance. 我非得工作挣零用钱。 3. She receives a monthly allowance of $500. 她每月收到500美元的津贴。 4. Your baggage allowance is 75 pounds. 你行李的重量限额是七十五英镑。', '过去式: allowanced 过去分词: allowanced 现在分词: allowancing 第三人称单数: allowances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hum', '[hʌm]', 'n.嗡嗡声；哼声；杂声 v.发低哼声；哼(曲子)；活跃 int.哼；嗯（用以表示犹豫）', '1. He could hear the hum of the bees in the garden. 他听得见花园里蜜蜂的嗡嗡声。 2. His strong voice cut through the hum of conversation like a knife through butter. 他那宏亮有力的声音一下子压倒了嗡嗡的谈话声。 3. The background with all of my phones is totally silent, no hiss, hum at all, just total blackness. 背景与我的所有电话，是完全沉默，没有噪音，哼声一切，在刚刚共有黑。 4. She heard the hum of voices in the house. 她听见了屋子里的嘈杂声。 5. You don\'t need to sing loud, you just hum softly. 你不必大声唱,只要轻轻哼就好了。 6. Hum, you\'re joking! 哼，你在开玩笑吧！', '形容词: hummable 名词: hummer 过去式: hummed 过去分词: hummed 现在分词: humming 第三人称单数: hums');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('president', '[\'prezɪdənt]', 'n.(国家)总统；(公司)总裁；校长；总经理；社长', '1. The president gave the Prince and his attendants a farewell banquet. 总统为王子和他的随员举行了告别宴会。 2. She was exalted to the position of president. 她被提升为校长。 3. The president has just come to see me. 校长刚才来看我来了。 4. When the president of the company retired, the vice-president was elevated to his position. 该公司的总经理退休时,副总经理被提升为总经理。', '名词: presidentship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('firm', '[fɜːrm]', 'n.公司；商行 adj.坚定的；结实的；坚固的；严格的 v.(使)变得坚实；确定 adv.稳固地；坚定地', '1. He has established his own firm. 他已建立起自己的公司。 2. He resigned his directorship and left the firm. 他放弃了董事职务, 离开了公司。 3. The businessment started out as an errand boy at the age of 14 in a firm. 这位大企业家从14岁时起就在一家商行里当听差。 4. We must maintain a firm attitude. 我们必须采取坚定的态度。 5. Exercise will firm up your muscles. 锻炼身体能使肌肉结实。 6. They made a firm pledge to support us. 他们做出了坚定地承诺支持我们。', '副词: firmly 比较级: firmer 最高级: firmest 名词: firmness 过去式: firmed 过去分词: firmed 现在分词: firming 第三人称单数: firms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wife', '[waɪf]', 'n.妻子；夫人', '1. He kissed his wife and children good-bye. 他吻别他的妻子和孩子。 2. The cruel man abandoned his wife and child. 那个狠心的男人抛弃了他的妻儿。 3. She tried to be an affectionate wife. 她试图做个温柔体贴的妻子。 4. He first met his wife in Rome. 他最初是在罗马碰到他的妻子的。', '名词: wifehood 名词复数: wives');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('boot', '[buːt]', 'n.靴子；猛踢；解雇；[英]汽车行李箱 vt.踢；穿靴子；逐出；启动(计算机)', '1. My foot won\'t go into this boot. 我的脚伸不进这只靴子。 2. Italy vaguely resembles a boot. 意大利国的形状像只靴子。 3. The door wouldn\'t open so I gave it a boot. 门开不了,所以我朝门猛踢一脚。 4. The thief gave me a boot in my stomach. 小偷朝我腹部踢了一脚。 5. He kept booting the ball into the crowd. 他总把球往人群中踢。', '过去式: booted 过去分词: booted 现在分词: booting 第三人称单数: boots');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('radar', '[\'reɪdɑːr]', 'n.雷达', '1. There are enemy aircraft on the radar screen. 雷达萤屏上出现了敌人的飞机。 2. They plotted aircraft movements by radar. 他们借雷达标示飞机的动向。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lid', '[lɪd]', 'n.盖子；眼睑 vt.给 ... 装盖子', '1. He slammed the lid down. 他砰的一声盖上了盖子。 2. She gave the lid a few gentle taps to loosen it. 她把盖子轻拍了几下使它松动。 3. The lid of this jam pot won\'t unscrew. 这果酱罐的盖子拧不开。 4. She lifted the lid of the pot to add some salt. 她掀起锅盖加点盐。 5. They forgot to lid the garbage can. 他们忘了盖垃圾桶了。', '过去式: lidded 过去分词: lidded 现在分词: lidding 第三人称单数: lids');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tramp', '[træmp]', 'n.徒步；流浪汉；淫妇；重脚步声 v.践踏；步行', '1. The boys took a tramp together over the hills. 男孩们一起徒步爬那些山岗。 2. She wants to go for a tramp in the country. 她想去乡间远足。 3. The tramp was benumbed by the cold. 那个流浪汉被冻僵了。 4. A tramp came to the door and asked for food. 一个流浪汉来到门前讨饭吃。 5. One must tramp down the earth over sown seed, which is good for the plants. 播种后一定要踩墒，这样有助于植物的生长。', '形容词: trampish 名词: tramper 过去式: tramped 过去分词: tramped 现在分词: tramping 第三人称单数: tramps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('enroll', '[ɪn\'roʊl]', 'v.登记；招收；入伍', '1. He enrolled our names. 他把我们的名字登记下来了。 2. He enrolled with an employment agency for a secretary. 他在职业介绍所登记要当秘书。 3. This school plan to enroll 100 students every year. 该校每年只招收100名学生。 4. His son was enrolled for military service a couple of years ago. 他儿子在两三年前应募入伍。', '名词: enrollee');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('finish', '[\'fɪnɪʃ]', 'v.完成；结束；最后加工；用完 n.结束；完成；最后一层涂饰', '1. When do you finish your college course? 你什么时候完成大学课程？ 2. She should finish with him he treats her very badly. 她应该和他断绝关系－－他对她太不好了。 3. I\'ve finished with gambling it\'s a waste of money. 我已经戒赌了－－赌博完全是浪费钱财。 4. That fever nearly finished him off. 那场热病几乎送了他的命。 5. He was in at the finish and witnessed the excitement of the fans. 比赛结束前他在场,亲眼目睹了球迷们的狂热。', '名词: finisher 过去式: finished 过去分词: finished 现在分词: finishing 第三人称单数: finishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('curriculum', '[kə\'rɪkjələm]', 'n.全部课程；课程', '1. Our curriculum comprises Politics, Chinese, English and History. 我们的课程共有四门：政治、汉语、英语、历史。 2. Our mathematics curriculum is much more complicated now. 我们的数学课现在复杂得多了。', '形容词: curricular 名词复数: curricula');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('erroneous', '[ɪ\'roʊniəs]', 'adj.错误的；不正确的', '1. We must oppose these erroneous trends of thought. 我们必须反对所有这些错误的思潮。 2. Sometimes this information may be erroneous. 有时候这种信息是错误的。 3. Some of the erroneous pictures of America are painted by others. 但是对美国的一些不正确的描述也来自外部世界。 4. So on bad CD-ROM drives it is possible that you receive erroneous results. 以至于使用不好的光驱抓轨，可能会接收到不正确的结果。', '副词: erroneously 名词: erroneousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('animal', '[\'ænɪml]', 'n.动物；牲畜 adj.动物的；野兽的', '1. The jackal is a wild animal in Africa and Asia. 豺狼是产于亚非的一种野生动物。 2. This small animal has a pair of brown eyes. 这只小动物有一双棕色的眼睛。 3. A pig is a domestic animal. 猪是一种家畜。 4. The animal is dangerous when cornered. 野兽一旦陷于绝境就会变得很危险。 5. Try to cut down on the amount of animal fats you eat. 尽量减少你食用的动物脂肪的量。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fog', '[fɔːɡ]', 'n.雾；朦胧；迷惑 v.以雾笼罩；使模糊；迷惑', '1. The headlamps penetrated the fog. 车的前灯的光射进雾中。 2. Fog will persist throughout the night. 雾将整夜不散。 3. They used dry ice to fog the stage. 他们用乾冰于舞台变得一片朦胧。 4. A full moon was beginning to rise and peered redly through the upper edges of fog. 一轮满月开始升起，带着红色的光芒在雾气上沿朦胧出现。 5. Steam has fogged the bathroom mirror. 水蒸气把浴室里的镜子遮住了。', '名词: fogger 过去式: fogged 过去分词: fogged 现在分词: fogging 第三人称单数: fogs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whenever', '[wen\'evər]', 'adv.无论何时 conj.每当；无论何时；随时', '1. It\'s not urgent we can do it next week or whenever. 不是急事--我们可以下星期做或其他时候做。 2. I\'d like to see you whenever it\'s convenient. 在你方便的时候我想来看看你。 3. She gets in a fret whenever we\'re late. 只要我们一迟到,她就焦虑不安。 4. She hated it whenever Spike got the jump on her. 无论何时斯派克抢在她之前，她都怀恨在心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('retention', '[rɪ\'tenʃn]', 'n.保留物；保存；保持(力)；记忆力', '1. The retention is withheld only for bonus situation. 滞留金只是为了发奖金。 2. Did you specify a reasonable retention age? 是否指定了合理的保持期? 3. Plan a retention policy for e-mail messages and log entries. 为电子邮件和日志项计划一个保持策略。 4. His retention of energy at this hour is really surprising. 人们惊叹他在这个时候还能保持如此旺盛的精力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('concerning', '[kən\'sɜːnɪŋ]', 'prep.关于，涉及，就…而言', '1. He heard nothing concerning this matter. 关于这件事他什么都没听到。 2. Let me see all the official documents concerning the sale of this land. 让我看看买卖这块土地的所有官方文件。 3. The sales manager asked his men to inform him of everything concerning the sales in time. 销售部经理让他手下的人把关于销售量的情况及时报告他。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bundle', '[\'bʌndl]', 'n.捆；束；包；大笔钱 v.捆；把 ... 扎成一捆；匆忙地走', '1. He collected a bundle of sticks. 他收集了一捆树枝。 2. I see a bundle of firewood on the floor. 我看见了一捆劈柴在地板上。 3. On the table there is a bundle of flower. 桌子上有一束花。 4. My uncle sent me a large bundle on my birthday. 我生日时叔父给我寄来一个大包裹。 5. Can you bundle up the sheets for me? 你能替我将这些单子捆起来吗?', '名词: bundler 过去式: bundled 过去分词: bundled 现在分词: bundling 第三人称单数: bundles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('probable', '[\'prɑːbəbl]', 'adj.很可能的 n.很可能的事', '1. The most probable discipline for its use is chemical engineering, but it can also be used in materials science, fuels science, and chemistry programs. 它的使用的最很可能的纪律是化学工程，但是它也能被在材料科学，燃料科学和化学计画方面使用。 2. The most probable discipline for its use is chemical engineering, but it can also be used in materials science, fuels science, and chemistry programs. 它的使用的最很可能的纪律是化学工程，但是它也能被在材料科学，燃料科学和化学计画方面使用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('graph', '[ɡræf]', 'n.图表；示意图 vt.(以图表)表示', '1. The graph shows a bulge in the price of meat. 图表显示肉类价格上涨。 2. Our research results are displayed in the form of a graph. 我们的研究结果已用图表列出. 3. This is a simple graph of legislative process. 这是立法过程的简易示意图。 4. This program provides a simple way to graph the flow chart. 这个程序提供了一种简单的方式用图表示流程图。', '过去式: graphed 过去分词: graphed 现在分词: graphing 第三人称单数: graphs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fireplace', '[\'faɪərpleɪs]', 'n.壁炉', '1. She edged her chair nearer to the fireplace. 她把椅子移近壁炉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('then', '[ðen]', 'adv.那么；然后；当时；而且 adj.当时的 n.当时', '1. He\'ll be looking for a new secretary then? 那么,他就要找个新秘书了？ 2. He took his hat and then left. 他拿起帽子，随即离开了。 3. We lived in the country then. 我们那时住在乡下。 4. I\'ve sent cards to all my family. Then there\'s your family and the neighbours. 我已给我全家人都寄去了请帖。还要给你家的人及邻居们寄。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soil', '[sɔɪl]', 'n.土地；土壤；污物，粪便 v.弄污', '1. It\'s rich there because of the fertility of soil. 因为土地肥沃，那儿很富裕。 2. Fertile soil yields good crops. 肥沃的土地能种出好庄稼。 3. This kind of soil contains much alkali. 这种土壤含碱丰富。 4. He transplanted the seedlings into peaty soil. 他把幼苗移栽到含泥炭的土壤里。 5. Her slanderous words soiled his reputation. 她中伤性的话损害了他的名誉。', '过去式: soiled 过去分词: soiled 现在分词: soiling 第三人称单数: soils');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('hail', '[heɪl]', 'n.冰雹 vi.下冰雹 vt.招呼；喝彩；宣称；来自 n.欢呼', '1. For three hours, the hail rattles on the roof. 一连三个小时，冰雹在屋顶上哗啦哗啦地下着。 2. The hail beat a loud tattoo on the windowpane. 冰雹在窗玻璃上嘈杂地连续敲打。 3. It\'s hailing outside. 外面在下冰雹。 4. An old friend hailed me from the other side of the street. 一个老朋友从街的对面喊我。 5. The youngsters greeted their idol with a hail. 那群年轻人向他们的偶像欢呼致敬。', '过去式: hailed 过去分词: hailed 现在分词: hailing 第三人称单数: hails');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('predecessor', '[\'predəsesər]', 'n.祖先；前任；原有事物', '1. The Yunxian Man fossil skull is believed by scientists to belong to homo erectus, a predecessor of homo sapiens that walked on their two legs with an upright body posture. 科学家们认为袁县人属于直立人，是靠两条腿直立行走的智力人的祖先。 2. Recently unearthed fossils trace whales to a doglike predecessor of hoofed plant-eaters, and genetic analysis has identified hippos as whales\' closest living relatives. 最近出土的化石使鲸的祖先可追溯到一种有蹄外形像狗的植食动物，而且基因分析证实了现存动物中河马是鲸的近亲。 3. He undid most of the good work of his predecessor. 他把前任的大部分业绩毁掉了。 4. Our new doctor is much younger than his predecessor. 我们新来的医生比他的前任年轻许多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('geography', '[dʒi\'ɑːɡrəfi]', 'n.地理', '1. How\'s the new geography teacher? 新的地理老师怎么样？ 2. The geography paper was difficult. 地理试题很难。 3. I have only a sketchy knowledge of geography. 我对地理只是一知半解。 4. He studied physical geography. 他研究自然地理。', '名词: geographer 名词复数: geographies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('protect', '[prə\'tekt]', 'v.保护；投保', '1. He raised his arm to protect his child from hurt. 他伸出手去，保护他的孩子免受伤害。 2. These gallant soldiers will protect our country. 这些勇敢的士兵会保卫我们的国家的。 3. These rare tigers are protected by special laws. 这些珍贵的老虎受到专门法律的保护。 4. Many of the homes weren\'t protected against flood damage. 许多家庭没有投水灾的保。', '副词: protectingly 过去式: protected 过去分词: protected 现在分词: protecting 第三人称单数: protects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pistol', '[\'pɪstl]', 'n.手枪', '1. A pistol shot rang out. 响起了手枪的声音。 2. It sounded like a small pistol going off. 那声音听起来像一支小手枪响。 3. He pushed forward the safety catch of his pistol. 他把他手枪的安全锁扣向前推了推。 4. The general came in, hipping a pistol. 将军走了进来,他的胯部佩带着一柄手枪。', '过去式: pistoled 过去分词: pistoled 现在分词: pistoling 第三人称单数: pistols');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('imagine', '[ɪ\'mædʒɪn]', 'vt.想像；设想；料想；猜想；认为 vi.想像', '1. You can imagine how surprised I was. 你可以想象我是多么惊讶。 2. It is hard to imagine the scale of the universe. 很难想像宇宙有多大。 3. Imagine yourself to be on a desert island. 设想一下你身处荒岛的情形。 4. I imagine he will come tomorrow. 我料想他明天会来。', '名词: imaginer 过去式: imagined 过去分词: imagined 现在分词: imagining 第三人称单数: imagines');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('tip', '[tɪp]', 'n.小费；小建议；轻拍；尖端，顶端；倾斜，翻倒 v.给小费；装顶端；倾斜；翻倒', '1. He charged me 20 yuan for tip. 他向我要了20元小费. 2. It\'s common to leave a tip in many Western countries. 在很多西方国家,给小费是很平常的。 3. This manual is full of useful tips. 这本小册子里有很多实用的小建议。 4. Did you remember to tip the porter? 你记得给搬运工小费了吗？', '名词: tipper 过去式: tipped 过去分词: tipped 现在分词: tipping 第三人称单数: tips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('modern', '[\'mɑːdərn]', 'adj.现代的；时髦的 n.现代人；时尚人士', '1. Modern agriculture is spoiling our beautiful countryside. 现代农业正在破坏我们美丽的农村。 2. He can\'t adjust himself to the whirl of modern life in this big city. 他无法适应这个大都市的现代生活的忙碌。 3. Her novel depicts life in modern London. 她的小说描写的是伦敦现代的生活。 4. She wears a modern dress. 她穿着一件时髦的礼服。 5. Education is essential to modern men. 教育对于现代人十分重要。', '副词: modernly 名词: modernness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('qualitative', '[\'kwɑːlətətɪv]', 'adj.性质上的；质的；定性的', '1. Indeed, every property is both qualitative and dispositional. 每个属性都是性质上的和趋势上的。 2. This will cause qualitative change. 这将会引起质的变化。 3. There are qualitative differences between the two products. 这两种产品存在着质的差别。 4. We can draw a few qualitative conclusions. 我们可以得出一些定性的结论。', '副词: qualitatively');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('separate', '[\'sepərət]', 'adj.分开的；不同的；单独的；各自的 v.分开；隔开；区分；分居；脱离 n.分开；抽印本', '1. Can these two definitions be conflated, or must they be kept separate? 这两个定义可以合成一个呢，还是必须分开? 2. I advocate separate classes for students to learn Chinese in different ways. 我建议我们分班授课，让不同的学生以不同的方式学习华文。 3. We don\'t have a separate dining room—the living area is all one. 我们没有单独的饭厅——活动空间都在一处。 4. The house is divided into two living units or residences, usually having separate entrances. 房屋分为两个居住部分,一般具有各自的出口。 5. We\'d better separate the good ones from the bad ones. 我们最好把好的和坏的分开。 6. Nothing can separate them from each other now. 现在什么也不能把他们彼此分开了。', '副词: separately 名词: separateness 过去式: separated 过去分词: separated 现在分词: separating 第三人称单数: separates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('smog', '[smɑːɡ]', 'n.烟雾', '1. Black smog reduced visibility to about fifty yards. 黑色的烟雾使能见度降到大约五十码左右。 2. The smog persisted throughout the day. 烟雾终日不散。', '形容词: smoggy');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('diary', '[\'daɪəri]', 'n.日记；日记簿', '1. His father ordered that he (should) keep a diary in English. 他的父亲规定他要用英文写日记。 2. I keep a diary every day. 我每天记日记。 3. There is no further reference to him in her diary. 她的日记中没有进一步提到他。 4. The preface of this diary recounted her life. 这本日记的前言叙述了她的生活。', '名词复数: diaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('payment', '[\'peɪmənt]', 'n.支付；支付的款项；报偿；报应', '1. They demand prompt payment. 他们要求立即付款。 2. You may defer payment until next week. 你可延期至下周支付。 3. We have still not yet received your payment. 我们仍未收到贵公司支付的款项。 4. The payment is made without official sanction. 该款是在没有官方允许情况下支付的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('gentle', '[\'dʒentl]', 'adj.温和的；轻柔的；温顺的；文雅的；出身名门的', '1. We\'ve never met such gentle people. 我们从来没有遇到这样温和的人。 2. My mother is a kind and gentle woman. 我的母亲是一位心地善良、性情温和的妇女。 3. The gentle music can relax him. 轻柔的音乐能使他放松。 4. A gentle breeze stirred the leaves. 微风吹动了树叶。', '副词: gently 比较级: gentler 最高级: gentlest 名词: gentleness 过去式: gentled 过去分词: gentled 现在分词: gentling 第三人称单数: gentles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('equivalent', '[ɪ\'kwɪvələnt]', 'adj.等价的 相等的 n.相等物', '1. Is there a French word that is the exact equivalent of the English word `home\'? 法语中有没有和英语home完全一样的对应词?', '副词: equivalently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bark', '[bɑːrk]', 'v.(狗)吠；咆哮 v.剥皮；擦伤 n.狗吠；咆哮 n.树皮', '1. The dog barked when the stranger came near. 当陌生人走近时，狗叫了起来。 2. An old dog does not bark for nothing. 老狗不会无事而吠。 3. When you speak to people, don\'t bark at them. 当你和人说话时不要咆哮。 4. Some officers bark out their orders. 有些军官以粗暴的声音发布命令。 5. He barked his elbow on the wall. 他碰到墙上，肘部擦破了皮。 6. Those trees have very beautiful white bark. 那些树长着非常漂亮的白色树皮。', '过去式: barked 过去分词: barked 现在分词: barking 第三人称单数: barks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('quarter', '[\'kwɔːrtər]', 'n.四分之一；一刻钟；一季；25美分；区；方向 v.四等分 adj.四分之一的', '1. Only a quarter of the earth is land. 仅仅地球的四分之一是陆地。 2. It\'s a quarter past ten. 现在是十点一刻。 3. The flight was put off about a quarter, because of ground fog. 由于地面有雾，这次班机推迟1 刻钟。 4. The rent is due at the end of each quarter. 缴纳租金以每季度末为期限。 5. We should quarter a pineapple. 我们应该把这个菠萝分成四等份。', '过去式: quartered 过去分词: quartered 现在分词: quartering 第三人称单数: quarters');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cock', '[kɑːk]', 'n.雄禽；公鸡；<粗俚>阴茎；旋塞 v.翘起；竖起', '1. The cock has brighter coloured feathers than the hen. 雄鸟的羽毛比雌鸟的艳丽。 2. The cock crowed at dawn. 公鸡在黎明时啼叫。 3. The test cock is on the inlet side of the shutoff valve. 测试旋塞位于关闭阀的进口一侧上。 4. The dog cocked its ears at the sound of footsteps. 狗听到脚步声竖起了耳朵。', '过去式: cocked 过去分词: cocked 现在分词: cocking 第三人称单数: cocks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fur', '[fɜːr]', 'n.毛皮；软毛；毛皮制品；皮衣 v.使生苔；使生垢', '1. He put on a coat with a fur lining. 他穿上一件有毛皮衬里的外衣。 2. She was wearing a silver fox fur across her shoulders. 她肩上披了一件银狐皮披肩。 3. The dog\'s fur was matted with blood. 那只狗的毛皮上沾有血迹。 4. The dog\'s fur bristled as it sensed danger. 那狗觉察到危险时，毛都竖立起来了。 5. The kettle was furred up. 壶里长了水锈。', '过去式: furred 过去分词: furred 现在分词: furring 第三人称单数: furs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rifle', '[\'raɪfl]', 'n.步枪 v.洗劫；抢劫', '1. Rifle reports could be heard in the distance. 听得见远处传来的步枪声。 2. He accidentally triggered his rifle. 他无意中扣发了他步枪的扳机。 3. The officer was fatally shot with an assault rifle yesterday morning while responding to the robbery in northeast Philadelphia. 在费城东北部，该警察昨天早晨在应付抢劫案的过程中遭到歹徒的来福枪的射击。', '名词: rifler 过去式: rifled 过去分词: rifled 现在分词: rifling 第三人称单数: rifles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fragment', '[\'fræɡmənt]', 'n.碎片；片段 v.使破碎；分裂', '1. She dropped the vase on the floor and it broke into fragments. 她把花瓶掉在地上，摔成了碎片。 2. There\'s a fragment of glass in the wound. 伤口内有玻璃碎片。 3. Her hand was cut by a fragment of glass. 她的手被一块玻璃碎片划破了。 4. I overheard a fragment of their conversation. 我无意中听到他们谈话的片段。 5. These bullets fragment on impact. 这些子弹射中物体时爆炸成碎片。', '过去式: fragmented 过去分词: fragmented 现在分词: fragmenting 第三人称单数: fragments');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('eminent', '[\'emɪnənt]', 'adj.著名的；卓越的', '1. Was an eminent landscape poet in ancient China. 是中国古代著名的山水诗作家。 2. Eminent physicists from all over the world came to the United States to celebrate the centennial of Einstein\'s birth. 全世界著名的物理学家来到美国庆祝爱因斯坦诞生一百周年。 3. Churchill was one of the world\'s most eminent statesmen. 邱吉尔是世界上最卓越的政治家之一。 4. Throughout the ages this eminent masterpiece has always held a special place in the hearts of Irish people. 各个时代，这一卓越的杰作都始终在爱尔兰民众的心中占据着一个特殊的位置。', '副词: eminently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transport', '[\'trænspɔːrt]', 'n.运输；心醉 v.运输；传播；流放；激动', '1. The goods have been cased up for transport. 货物已装箱待运。 2. London Transport run extra trains during the rush-hour. 伦敦运输公司在交通高峰时 间增开加班列车。 3. Please find alternative means of transport. 请另外找一个运输方法。 4. The transport of goods by air is very expensive. 空运货物费用十分昂贵。 5. A helicopter was used to transport the wounded. 一架直升飞机被用来运送伤员。', '形容词: transportable 名词: transportability 过去式: transported 过去分词: transported 现在分词: transporting 第三人称单数: transports');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anybody', '[\'enibɑːdi]', 'pron.任何人', '1. He didn\'t want to team up with anybody. 他不想与任何人合作。 2. By anybody\'s standards that work of art is A-1. 那件艺术品按任何人的标准都是第一流的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('token', '[\'toʊkən]', 'n.象征；标志；纪念品；代币；代价券；[语言学]语言符号 adj.象征性的；装样子的', '1. He gave me a necklace as a token of his affection.. 他给了我一根项链作为爱情的象征。 2. We sent the poor girl a birthday present in token of friendship. 我们送给那个可怜的小女孩一份生日礼物作为友谊的表示。 3. These flowers are a small token of my gratitude. 谨以此花聊表谢忱。 4. He gave his friend a book as a go-away token. 他送朋友一本书作为临别纪念。 5. The government agreed to send a small token force to the area. 政府同意派遣一小支象征性的部队到那一地区。', '过去式: tokened 过去分词: tokened 现在分词: tokening 第三人称单数: tokens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('principal', '[\'prɪnsəpl]', 'adj.主要的；首要的 n.本金；资本；校长；主角；委托人；主犯', '1. Our principal problem is lack of time. 我们的主要问题就是缺少时间。 2. My wages are the principal source of my income. 薪金是我收入的主要来源。 3. My principal concern is my family\'s welfare. 我至为关心的是我一家的幸福。 4. How much interest will there be on a principal of $5000? 5000美元本金的利息是多少？', '副词: principally 名词: principalship');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dramatic', '[drə\'mætɪk]', 'adj.戏剧性的；引人注目的；给人深刻印象的；激动人心的 dramatics: n.；戏剧作品；戏剧艺术；戏剧性的行为', '1. After a dramatic pause, the lawyer finished her summation. 在戏剧性的沉默之后,这位律师作完了她的总述。 2. Her opening words were dramatic. 她的开场白十分动听。 3. It was really a dramatic game. 那确实是场给人印象深刻比赛。 4. She made a dramatic speech at the meeting. 她在会上发表了激动人心的演说。 5. Shakespeare\'s dramatics is very popular among the young people. 莎士比亚的戏剧作品在年轻人中很流行。', '副词: dramatically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('passion', '[\'pæʃn]', 'n.激情；热情；酷爱；盛怒', '1. The dying embers of the former passion can still be seen in his articles. 往日激情将熄的余烬仍可从他的文章中看出来。 2. Life needs curiosity, enthusiasm and passion, which depends on how we think of the world. 生活需要好奇心、热情和激情,这都取决于我们怎么看待这个世界。 3. I have a passion for American literature. 我酷爱美国文学。 4. His passion for reading never deserted him. 他从未放弃过对读书的热爱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('write', '[raɪt]', 'v.写；书写；填写；作曲', '1. I\'ve been writing for three hours. 我已经写了三个小时了。 2. Nature inspired him to write such beautiful poems. 自然赋予他灵感,使他写出如此优美的诗句。 3. But there are some parts of the world where even now people cannot write. 但直到现在,世界上有些地方的人们还不会书写。 4. The new doctor smiled smugly as he continued to write on his clipboard. 这位新医生得意地笑了笑,接着填写病例卡。', '过去式: wrote 过去分词: written/writ 现在分词: writing 第三人称单数: writes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('reporter', '[rɪ\'pɔːrtər]', 'n.记者', '1. The reporter had a red-hot story. 那个记者掌握著最新消息。', '形容词: reportorial 副词: reportorially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('latent', '[\'leɪtnt]', 'adj.潜伏的；潜在的', '1. He was infected with a latent infection. 他被感染了一种潜伏性的传染病。 2. We must take measures to control the latent disease germs. 我们必须采取措施控制潜伏的病菌。 3. Within everyone there was a latent volcano of unhappiness and discontent. 在每个人心中都有一座潜伏着不幸福与不满的火山。 4. The latent cause of crime is often avarice. 贫婪常是犯罪的潜在诱因。', '副词: latently');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('purchase', '[\'pɜːrtʃəs]', 'vt.购买 n.购买；购买的物品', '1. She purchased a number of shares in the company. 她在公司里买了一些股票。 2. Tickets must be purchased two weeks in advance. 票必须提前两周买。 3. The receipt is your proof of purchase. 这张发票是你购物的凭据. 4. The house is the most expensive purchase I have ever made. 房子是我买过的最贵的东西。', '名词: purchaser 过去式: purchased 过去分词: purchased 现在分词: purchasing 第三人称单数: purchases');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('connection', '[kə\'nekʃn]', 'n.联系；关系；连接；亲戚', '1. What is the connection between the two ideas? 这两个概念之间有何联系？ 2. There is no connection between them. 他们之间没有什么关系。 3. Your connection with the press served out turn. 你与新闻界的关系正适应了我们的需要。 4. I have no immediate connection with him. 我和他没有直接关系。', '形容词: connectional');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bring', '[brɪŋ]', 'vt.带来；促使；引起；劝诱 vi.产生', '1. She brought her boyfriend to the party. 她带着男朋友来参加聚会。 2. Rot it! I forgot to bring my book with me. 糟了!忘记带书来了。 3. Floods brought destruction to the vally. 洪水给山谷造了大灾害。 4. Smoke and flames brought the neighbors. 浓烟和火焰引起了邻居们的注意 5. Indigestion may bring about this disease. 消化不良可能引起这种病。', '名词: bringer 过去式: brought 过去分词: brought 现在分词: bringing 第三人称单数: brings');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('weave', '[wiːv]', 'v.编织；组合；编造；迂回前进 n.编法；织法；编织', '1. Spiders weave webs. 蜘蛛结网。 2. She can tell you how to weave reeds into a beautiful basket. 她能教你怎样用芦苇编织漂亮的篮子。 3. I try to weave all of the concepts together. 我想把所有的想法编织在一起。 4. I think you can weave a story around this incident. 我想你可以围绕这一事件编一个故事。 5. A third form of weave is the satin weave. 第三种织造形式是缎纹组织。', '过去式: wove 过去分词: woven 现在分词: weaving 第三人称单数: weaves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grocer', '[\'ɡroʊsər]', 'n.食品杂货商；杂货店', '1. She is a Chinese grocer\'s daughter. 她是个华裔食品杂货商的女儿。 2. The grocer sparred with her outside his store. 杂货商在店外和她吵起来了。 3. There\'s a grocer\'s at the corner of the street. 在街道的转弯处有一个食品杂货店。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shortage', '[\'ʃɔːrtɪdʒ]', 'n.不足；缺少，短缺', '1. The war was lost because of a shortage of munitions. 战争因军火不足而失败。 2. Power shortage browned out the city that winter. 那年冬天，由于电力不足，市里采取了部分停电供应措施。 3. He always bemoans the shortage of funds for research. 他总是叹息研究经费不足。 4. Continuance of the war will mean shortage of the food. 战争的持续意味着食品短缺。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('professional', '[prə\'feʃənl]', 'adj.职业的；专业的；专门的 n.专业人员', '1. Don\'t wear those clothes to work; try to look more professional! 别穿这些衣服去工作，要穿得象个专业人员的样子。 2. That doctor has been accused of professional misconduct. 那位医生被指控违反医德。 3. She was always punctual and professional. 她总是准时并具有专业能力。 4. He is a professional journalist. 他是一位专门的新闻从业人员。 5. She is a real professional. 她是个真正的专家。', '副词: professionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('loom', '[luːm]', 'n.织布机 n.若隐若现 vi.隐约可见；迫近', '1. I don\'t know how to use a hand loom. 我不知道怎样使用手工织布机。 2. The fabric was weaving at her loom. 她的织布机正编织着这些织物。 3. The shuttle flies back and forth on the loom. 织布机上梭子来回飞动。 4. The children are so excited to watch for the first loom of the land. 孩子们兴奋地注视着陆地的初现。 5. The mountainous island loomed on the horizon. 那座巨大的岛屿隐隐约约浮现在地平线上。', '过去式: loomed 过去分词: loomed 现在分词: looming 第三人称单数: looms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('instance', '[\'ɪnstəns]', 'n.例子；场合；情况；要求；诉讼程序 vt.举例说明', '1. This is only one instance out of many. 这不过是许多例子中的一个。 2. Can you quote a recent instance? 你能举出一个最近的例证吗? 3. You may get along well with your boss but there will always be that specific instance where you want to say more than you should. 也许你和你老板相处得很好，但总是会有一些特殊的场合，你想说的话多于你应该说的。 4. In most instances the pain soon goes away. 在多数情况下,这种疼痛很快就会消失。 5. The game was exciting, as was instanced by the score. 依分数所示, 这场比赛是很紧张的。', '过去式: instanced 过去分词: instanced 现在分词: instancing 第三人称单数: instances');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fatal', '[\'feɪtl]', 'adj.致命的；毁灭性的；决定性的', '1. We gave the enemy a fatal blow. 我们给敌人以致命的打击。 2. There is a fatal flaw in the plan. 计划中有一个致命的缺陷。 3. A possibly fatal crisis may be at hand. 毁灭性的危机可能近在咫尺。 4. The fatal day of the election finally arrived. 大选决定命运的一天终于来到了。', '副词: fatally 名词: fatality');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('priest', '[priːst]', 'n.教士；神父；牧师；僧侣；泰斗', '1. A priest exorcized the ghost from the house. 教士将鬼从房屋中驱走。 2. The priest confessed the young man. 神父听取那个青年的忏悔。 3. The priest pronounced them man and wife. 神父宣布他们已结为夫妇。 4. The priest persuaded him to give up his bad habit. 牧师劝他放弃坏习惯。', '过去式: priested 过去分词: priested 现在分词: priesting 第三人称单数: priests');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elect', '[ɪ\'lekt]', 'v.选举；选择 adj.精选的；当选的；[神学]被上帝选中的 n.被选中者；[神学]上帝的选民', '1. They elected him chairman. 他们选他做主席。 2. They organized a poll to elect a president. 他们组织了一次投票选举总统。 3. You can\'t elect to deal at some other rate. 不能选择其他价格。 4. The President elect will be installed next week. 候任总统将在下周正式就任。 5. Voters in New Jersey and Virginia will head to the polls to elect governors. 新泽西州和弗吉利亚的选民将投票选出他们的州长。', '过去式: elected 过去分词: elected 现在分词: electing 第三人称单数: elects');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sympathetic', '[ˌsɪmpə\'θetɪk]', 'adj.同情的；共鸣的；赞同的 n.交感神经', '1. He took a sympathetic attitude toward my situation. 他对我的境遇抱同情的态度. 2. We are sympathetic with the flood sufferers. 我们同情水灾受难者。 3. She was sympathetic to my ideas. 她对我的想法表示支持。 4. They were quite sympathetic to our proposals. 他们非常赞同我们的建议。', '副词: sympathetically');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fringe', '[frɪndʒ]', 'n.流苏；边缘；次要；额外补贴 vt.用流苏修饰；镶边', '1. The girl wore her hair in a fringe. 那个女孩子额前梳着刘海。 2. The edge of the carpet was frayed into a fringe. 地毯的边缘被散编成一绺绺流苏。 3. They put up tent on the fringe of the woods. 他们在树林边缘搭起帐篷。 4. A fringe of trees stood round the pool. 池塘四周耸立着一圈树木。 5. Coconut palms fringe the shoreline. 岸边点缀着椰子树。', '形容词: fringy 过去式: fringed 过去分词: fringed 现在分词: fringing 第三人称单数: fringes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('grin', '[ɡrɪn]', 'v.露齿而笑；(以咧嘴笑来)表示 n.露齿笑；咧嘴笑', '1. They grinned with pleasure when I gave them the sweets. 当我给他们糖果时，他们高兴地咧开嘴笑了。 2. He grin at me, as if sharing a secret joke. 他朝我龇牙一笑，好像彼此会心领略一个笑话。 3. When the rain returns, I will grin even more? 天再下雨时，我会咧嘴笑得更多? 4. He grin at me, as if sharing a secret joke. 他朝我龇牙一笑，好像彼此会心领略一个笑话。 5. He twisted his face into a grin. 他扭歪着脸露齿而笑。', '副词: grinningly 名词: grinner 过去式: grinned 过去分词: grinned 现在分词: grinning 第三人称单数: grins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('optimistic', '[ˌɑːptɪ\'mɪstɪk]', 'adj.乐观的；乐观主义的', '1. The book ended on an optimistic note. 该书的结尾寓意乐观。 2. The stockholders are optimistic about the company\'s future. 股东对公司的前景很乐观。 3. We are still optimistic, whatever the result (may be). 我们仍然乐观，不论结果如何。 4. I was exhausted and relieved, but I wasn\'t wildly optimistic. 我已感到精疲力尽,同时也感到如释重负,然而,我并不抱盲目乐观的态度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('avert', '[ə\'vɜːrt]', 'vt.转开；避免；防止', '1. It was Scott\'s turn to avert his gaze. 这下轮到斯科特移开他注视的目光了。 2. The government has failed to avert a national strike. 政府没有能够避免这场全国性的罢工。 3. He managed to avert suspicion. 他设法避嫌。 4. The lake will be dyked to avert floods. 将为此湖筑堤以防洪水。', '形容词: avertible 过去式: averted 过去分词: averted 现在分词: averting 第三人称单数: averts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('beverage', '[\'bevərɪdʒ]', 'n.饮料', '1. What beverage would you like? 你想喝什么饮料？ 2. The bar steward is accountable to the beverage manager. 酒吧间服务员要对餐饮部经理负责。 3. He never drinks alcoholic beverage. 他从不喝含酒精的饮料。 4. The beverage is often colored with caramel. 这种饮料常用焦糖染色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('patience', '[\'peɪʃns]', 'n.耐心；忍耐；毅力', '1. Her endless patience made her the best nurse in the hospital. 无限的耐心使她成为这个医院最好的护士。 2. His patience was worn out by all these troubles. 这么多麻烦使他都没有耐心了。 3. She owes her success to hard work and patience. 她的成功是努力工作和耐心的结果。 4. Patience is a plaster for all sores. 忍耐可以减轻一切痛苦。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pole', '[poʊl]', 'n.杆；柱；极点 v.(用杆)支撑 Pole. n.波兰人', '1. Pole vaulters need long run-ups. 撑竿跳需要长距离助跑。 2. The hut was made of poles covered with grass mats. 茅屋用木杆搭成，上面以草席覆盖。 3. He had put up a basket on a pole in the back yard. 他在后院一根柱子上安一个球篮。 4. When Scott reached the South Pole he found Amundsen had anticipated him. 当斯科特抵达南极的时候，发现阿蒙森比他到得更早。', '过去式: poled 过去分词: poled 现在分词: poling 第三人称单数: poles');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('express', '[ɪk\'spres]', 'n.快车；快递；专使 adj.明确的；急速的；直接的 adv.用快递 vt.表达；表示；挤压出；快递', '1. The express is as swift as an arrow. 快车似箭一般地飞驶。 2. We have to change here for an express. 我们必须在这里换乘快车。 3. I sent the letter by express. 我这封信寄的是快递。 4. Important documents will be sent by express. 重要文件会以快递寄出。 5. Matthew left express instructions to keep all doors locked. 马修下达了明确的指示,让我们把所有的门都锁上。 6. The parcel was sent express. 这包裹是用快邮寄的. 7. Many theologies express the same ideas. 许多宗教理论表达同一种思想。', '形容词: expressible 名词: expresser 过去式: expressed 过去分词: expressed 现在分词: expressing 第三人称单数: expresses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('delight', '[dɪ\'laɪt]', 'n.高兴；快乐 v.(使)高兴；(使)欣喜', '1. She clapped her hands in delight. 她高兴地拍手。 2. The children were prancing about with delight. 孩子们高兴得蹦蹦跳跳。 3. He takes great delight in painting. 他爱好绘画。 4. We delight in going for long walks in the country. 我们乐于去乡间远足。', '过去式: delighted 过去分词: delighted 现在分词: delighting 第三人称单数: delights 形容词: delightful 副词: delightfully');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('detector', '[dɪ\'tektər]', 'n.探测器', '1. Thermopile is usually a blackened thermal detector. 热堆一般是个涂黑了的热探测器。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('clause', '[klɔːz]', 'n.条款；[语]从句', '1. There is a contentious clause in the treaty. 这条约中有一条有争议的条款。 2. A penalty clause was written into the contract. 在合同中写入了一项罚款条款。 3. Please pay attention to this clause in the sentence. 请注意看句中的这个从句。 4. This is an attributive clause. 这是一个定语从句。', '形容词: clausal');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rejoice', '[rɪ\'dʒɔɪs]', 'v.（使）高兴；（使）欢喜', '1. I always rejoice in my comrades\' achievements. 我总是为同志们的成就感到高兴。 2. We rejoiced at the good news. 我们为这个好消息而高兴。 3. They all rejoiced to hear the happy news. 他们都很乐于听到这个令人高兴的消息。 4. It rejoices my heart to hear that my son is still alive. 听到儿子仍活着，我心很高兴。', '名词: rejoicer 过去式: rejoiced 过去分词: rejoiced 现在分词: rejoicing 第三人称单数: rejoices');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('persist', '[pər\'sɪst]', 'v.坚持；执意；继续；持续', '1. I hope you\'ll persist in your efforts. 我希望你们再接再励。 2. He will persist in riding that dreadful bicycle. 他执意要骑那辆破自行车。 3. If you persist, you will annoy them even more. 你若固执，他们就更恼火了。 4. If you persist in breaking the law you will go to prison. 如果你再继续违法的话，你会坐牢的。', '名词: persister 过去式: persisted 过去分词: persisted 现在分词: persisting 第三人称单数: persists');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nickname', '[\'nɪkneɪm]', 'n. 绰号； 昵称 v. 给 ... 取绰号', '1. We often call him by his nickname. 我们经常叫他的绰号。 2. Everyone on the team was tagged with a nickname. 队里的每个成员都给起了一个绰号。 3. Jess is just my nickname - my real name is Jessica. 杰西只是我的昵称，我的真名是杰西卡。 4. Your nickname lets a person worry for you. 你的昵称让人替你担心。', '名词: nicknamer 过去式: nicknamed 过去分词: nicknamed 现在分词: nicknaming 第三人称单数: nicknames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sacred', '[\'seɪkrɪd]', 'adj.神圣的；受尊重的', '1. In India the cow is a sacred animal. 在印度，牛是神圣的动物。 2. We use them to protect our sacred grounds. 我们使用它们来保卫我们神圣的土地。 3. Nothing is sacred to these wild youths. 这些狂野的年轻人什么都不尊重。 4. This area was hallowed by sacred memories. 这个地区由于宗教上的纪念意义而被视为圣地。', '副词: sacredly 名词: sacredness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mouth', '[maʊθ]', 'n.嘴；口；开口；河口 v.不出声说；装腔作势地说；喃喃地说', '1. Her mouth is her best feature. 她的嘴是她容貌上最好看的部分。 2. The dying animal was found foaming at the mouth. 那只将死的动物被发现口吐白沫。 3. Seeing that we are confused about her attitude, she had to give mouth to her doubts. 看到我们对她的态度表示不解,她只得说出心里的疑惑。 4. The sand has silted up the mouth of the river. 泥沙已把河口堵住了。 5. The nurse mouthed the word \"quiet\". 护士以口形默示“安静”。', '名词复数: mouths 过去式: mouthed 过去分词: mouthed 现在分词: mouthing 第三人称单数: mouths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('January', '[\'dʒænjueri]', 'n.一月', '1. It\'s quite warm for January. 就一月份来说，天气相当暖和了。 2. I was born on January eleventh. 我生于一月十一日。 3. The station will be operative again in January. 该车站将于一月份恢复使用。', '名词复数: Januaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('decision', '[dɪ\'sɪʒn]', 'n.决定；决心；判决', '1. I don\'t think his decision is wise in reality. 实际上,我觉得他的决定并不明智。 2. We can\' t reach a decision without our chairman. 主席不在场 3. All is dependent on your decision. 一切看你的决心而定。 4. The judge will give his decision tomorrow. 法官将于明天做出判决。', '形容词: decisional 过去式: decisioned 过去分词: decisioned 现在分词: decisioning 第三人称单数: decisions');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('attendance', '[ə\'tendəns]', 'n.出席；出席人数；出席率', '1. My attendance at school is excellent. 我在学校的出席情况极好。 2. Attendance at the meeting is mandatory. 出席会议是必要的 3. The number of the attendance will run to eighty. 这些出席人数约有八十名。 4. The attendance was encouragingly high. 出席人数之多令人振奋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('compact', '[\'kɑːmpækt]', 'adj.紧密的；紧凑的；简洁的 vt.使简洁；使装满；压实 n.合约条约；梳妆粉盒；<美>小型汽车', '1. He received a compact package. 他收到一个扎得很紧的包裹。 2. As writers, they like a structure that is compact. 写文章的时候，他们喜欢采用紧凑的结构。 3. Regulator shall be corrosion resistant, compact and lightweight. 这种调节阀应该是耐腐蚀的，紧凑的和轻型的。 4. We\'d love to buy a compact car. 我们想买一辆简洁的车。 5. The kids are try to compact the sand into the mold. 孩子们正在设法把这沙土堆积到模子里。 6. You should sign your name on the right side of the compact. 你应该在合约的右边签上你的名字。', '副词: compactly 名词: compactness 过去式: compacted 过去分词: compacted 现在分词: compacting 第三人称单数: compacts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pump', '[pʌmp]', 'n.泵；抽水机；打气筒；抽水；打气 v.打气；唧筒般运动；灌输；抽取；增加；<口>盘问', '1. The heart has acted as a strong pump. 心脏充当了一部强有力的泵。 2. At the farm there was an old-fashioned pump for drawing water from a well. 那个农场有一台老式的用来从井里抽水的抽水机。 3. Can you lend me your bicycle pump? 能把你的打气筒借给我吗？ 4. After several pumps, the water began to flow. 用泵抽了几下之后,水流出来了。 5. Pump the tire up hard before going out on the road. 在出去上路之前, 要把轮胎打足气。', '名词: pumper 过去式: pumped 过去分词: pumped 现在分词: pumping 第三人称单数: pumps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('army', '[\'ɑːrmi]', 'n.军队；陆军；一大批', '1. The battlefield is full of the army. 军队布满了战场。 2. He joined the army a year ago. 一年以前，他参军了。 3. The head of state was deposed by the army. 国家元首被军队废黜了。 4. The town was pillaged by the invading army. 入侵的军队将该城镇掠夺一空。', '名词复数: armies');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('evidence', '[\'evɪdəns]', 'n.证据；证词；根据；迹象 v.证明；证实', '1. There wasn\'t enough evidence to prove his guilt. 没有充分的证据能证明他有罪。 2. Evidence weighted against the defendant. 证词很不利于被告。 3. It is a statement in conflict with other evidence. 这一陈述与其他证词不一致。 4. Have you any evidence to support this statement? 你这种说法有根据吗? 5. His answer evidenced a guilty conscience. 他的回答证明他良心有愧。', '过去式: evidenced 过去分词: evidenced 现在分词: evidencing 第三人称单数: evidences');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ambitious', '[æm\'bɪʃəs]', 'adj.有雄心的；野心勃勃的；有抱负的', '1. Mr. Lin is an ambitious businessman. 林先生是个有雄心的生意人。 2. I ought to do something a bit more ambitious. 我应当做些更有雄心的事。 3. They ventured on an ambitious program of reform. 他们冒然采取一项野心勃勃的改革计划。 4. The ambitious boy learned very quickly. 那位有抱负的少年学得很快。', '副词: ambitiously 名词: ambitiousness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('Christ', '[kraɪst]', 'n.基督；救世主 int.天啊！', '1. Christ\'s message was that God loved the world. 耶稣基督的启示就是神爱世人。 2. The pope is known as the vicar of Christ. 教皇被称做基督的代理者。 3. To Christians, Jesus Christ is the Savior. 对基督徒来说，主耶稣是他们的救世主。 4. There was christ in the metal shell. 披着盔甲的救世主。', '形容词: Christlike 名词: Christlikeness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('century', '[\'sentʃəri]', 'n.百年；世纪 adj.百年的', '1. This book was written centuries ago. 这本书是几百年前写的。 2. Many centuries have passed since that time. 从那时起，几百年过去了。 3. He flourished in the early 18th century. 他在18世纪早期享有盛名。 4. The palace was built in the fifteenth century. 这宫殿建于十五世纪。', '形容词: centurylong 名词复数: centuries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bloom', '[bluːm]', 'n.花；开花；最佳时期；花期 v.开花；繁盛', '1. The apple-trees are out of bloom. 苹果树已经落了花。 2. Most roses will begin to bloom from late May. 大多数玫瑰从五月末开始开花。 3. The roses are in full bloom. 玫瑰花盛开了。 4. The apple trees are in full bloom at the moment. 目前苹果树开满了花。 5. Daffodils and crocuses bloom in the spring. 水仙花和番红花在春天开放。', '形容词: bloomy 过去式: bloomed 过去分词: bloomed 现在分词: blooming 第三人称单数: blooms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('vocal', '[\'voʊkl]', 'adj.声音的；口头的；声乐的；直言不讳的 n.元音；声乐作品', '1. The tongue is one of the vocals. 舌头是发声器官之一。 2. In the present instance he took no notice of my abrupt vocal response. 在目前这个情况下，他不去注意我那突兀的口头回答。 3. I like instrumental music better than vocal music. 我喜欢器乐胜于声乐。 4. He has been very vocal in his criticism of the government\'s policy. 他对政府政策的批评一直是直言不讳。 5. I select the two artists who have the commeasurable from the multitudinous outstanding vocal music performing artists to analyze and compare. 然而，她们却在声乐作品演唱方面表现出了不尽相同的理解，并形成和确立了截然不同的个人演唱风格。', '副词: vocally 名词: vocalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('girl', '[ɡɜːrl]', 'n.女孩；少女；姑娘；女儿；女职员；女朋友；老婆；老母亲；老妇人 adj.女的；女孩的；雌性的', '1. The girl has a light hand for knitting. 这女孩手巧，精于编织。 2. My father left me forever when I was only a girl. 在我还是小女孩时,我父亲就已去世了。 3. This picture represents a girl playing the piano. 这幅画描绘一个在弹钢琴的少女。 4. The girl stood shivering with cold on the doorstep. 那姑娘站在门前的台阶上,冷得直打哆嗦。 5. There are 25 girl students in our class as against only 5 in Class Two. 我们班有25名女学生，而二班只有5名。', '名词: girlhood');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('miniature', '[\'mɪnətʃər]', 'adj.小型的；小规模的 n.缩图；小画像；小模型', '1. The little girl has a miniature camera. 小女孩有个小型照相机。 2. The child was playing with his miniature railway. 这孩子正在玩他的小型玩具铁路。 3. The room resembled a miniature battlefield. 这个房间很像一个缩小了的战场。 4. She is just like her mother in miniature. 她简直是她母亲的缩影。', '名词: miniaturist');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('neat', '[niːt]', 'adj.整洁的；简洁的；利索的 adv.整洁地；利索地', '1. He has made neat paths and has built a wooden bridge over a pool. 他在花园里铺上整洁的小路，并在池塘上架起木桥。 2. The headmaster praised the boys for their neat turn-out. 校长表扬男同学服装整齐。 3. He gave a neat summary of the financial situation. 他对财务状况做了简要的概括。 4. The naughty boy played a neat trick. 这个淘气的小男孩玩了一个巧妙的花招。 5. he slipped the ball back neat. 他把球利索地传了回来。', '副词: neatly 比较级: neater 最高级: neatest 名词: neatness 名词复数: neat');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('search', '[sɜːrtʃ]', 'v.搜寻；探求；调查 n.搜寻；搜索；调查', '1. They searched the woods for the little boy. 他们在森林中搜寻到了那个小男孩。 2. She searched through the pile of papers and found his letter underneath. 她在一堆文件里搜寻，终于在底下找到了他的信。 3. He spent his life searching after truth. 他一生探求真理。 4. Let me search into this matter for you. 让我为你调查这件事。 5. The search proved fruitless. 搜寻没有结果。', '形容词: searchable 名词: searcher 过去式: searched 过去分词: searched 现在分词: searching 第三人称单数: searches');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ascend', '[ə\'send]', 'v.上升；攀登', '1. The stairs in the hotel ascend in a graceful curve. 这个旅店的楼梯以优美的曲线上升。 2. It is easier to descend than to ascend. 下降容易上升难。 3. A small party is planning to ascend Mount Everest. 一小伙人正计划攀登珠穆朗玛峰。 4. Setting foot on the island, he began to ascend the trail. 他踏上荒岛，开始顺着小径往上攀登。', '形容词: ascendable 过去式: ascended 过去分词: ascended 现在分词: ascending 第三人称单数: ascends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mix', '[mɪks]', 'v.混合；掺入；合成；联系；融合；介入 n.混合(物)；融合', '1. You can\'t mix oil with water. 你不能把油和水混合。 2. If you mix blue with yellow, you\'ll get green. 蓝色和黄色混合在一起就成了绿色。 3. For better flavor, you can mix an egg into the batter. 要想口味更好,你可以在面糊中加进一个鸡蛋。 4. Her son\'s return made her mix joy with sorrow. 她儿子的归来令她喜悲交集。 5. Alcohol and drugs is a deadly mix. 酒精和毒品混在一块儿,足以令人毙命。', '形容词: mixable 过去式: mixed 过去分词: mixed 现在分词: mixing 第三人称单数: mixes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('illegal', '[ɪ\'liːɡl]', 'adj.非法的；不合法的 n.非法移民', '1. The jewellery firm is just a front for their illegal trade in diamonds. 该珠宝公司不过是进行非法的钻石交易的幌子。 2. All protests are brutally repressed by the government as illegal. 所有的抗议活动都遭到当局的野蛮镇压，并被宣布为非法。 3. Their speculative buying of grain is illegal. 他们投机购买谷物是不合法的。 4. Abortion is illegal in this country. 人工流产在这个国家是不合法的。 5. The illegals couldn\'t be admitted by the authority. 非法移民是不被政府认可的。', '副词: illegally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('competition', '[ˌkɑːmpə\'tɪʃn]', 'n.竞争；比赛', '1. Everyone in modern society faces keen competitions. 现代社会的每个人都面临着激烈的竞争。 2. To our satisfaction, he had got the first prize in the diving competition. 我们满意的是,他在跳水比赛中获得了一等奖。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('lash', '[læʃ]', 'n.鞭子；鞭打；睫毛；讽刺 v.鞭打；摆动；抨击', '1. By rod and lash, the boy was punished. 木棍和鞭子用来惩罚这个男孩。 2. The pirate captain beat his crew with a lash. 海盗船长用鞭子抽打他的船员。 3. With a lash of its tail the tiger leaped at her. 老虎把尾巴一甩朝她扑过来。 4. Does the Lash Extender come in other colors apart from black ? 睫毛增长液除黑色外，还有什么其它颜色？ 5. He began to lash Luke unmercifully across buttocks and thighs. 他开始无情地鞭打卢克的屁股和大腿。', '过去式: lashed 过去分词: lashed 现在分词: lashing 第三人称单数: lashes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('politician', '[ˌpɑːlə\'tɪʃn]', 'n.政治家；政客', '1. A politician should be a servant of the people. 政治家应是人民的公仆。 2. That famous politician was murdered last year. 那位著名的政治家去年被谋杀了。 3. A politician needs the common touch. 政治家需要有平易近人的美德。 4. The politician gave an equivocal answer. 那政客的答复模棱两可。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('never', '[\'nevər]', 'adv.永不；绝不；从不；未曾', '1. I will never forget your kindness. 我永远忘不了你的好意。 2. In these altitudes snow never melts. 在这样的高度，雪永不融化。 3. His love for science will never die. 他对科学的热爱永不会消退。 4. We will never yield to invaders. 我们绝不会向侵略者屈服。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('February', '[\'februeri]', 'n.二月', '1. The second month of the year is February. 一年的第二个月是二月。 2. They reached Beijing on February 17. 他们于二月十七日到达北京。', '名词复数: Februaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('task', '[tæsk]', 'n.任务；工作 vt.交给某人（任务)；使做艰苦的工作', '1. It\'s an arduous task. 这是一项艰巨的任务。 2. It is an irksome task. 那是件令人厌烦的工作。 3. Her work is a laborious task. 她的工作很艰苦。 4. This is a task well within your ability. 这完全是你力所能及的工作。 5. We should devote all our efforts to task. 我们应该全力以赴地工作。', '过去式: tasked 过去分词: tasked 现在分词: tasking 第三人称单数: tasks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('faculty', '[\'fæklti]', 'n.（大学的）系或院；全体教员；才能；能力', '1. He is the dean of the Faculty of Medicine. 他是医学院院长。 2. We haven\'t set up the Faculty of Law in our university. 我们学校还没下设法学院。 3. Both faculty and students oppose the measures. 全体教师和学生都反对这种方法。 4. She has the faculty to learn languages easily. 她有轻而易举学会语言的才能。', '名词复数: faculties');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('factor', '[\'fæktər]', 'n.因素；因数；因子 vt.把 ... 因素包括进去 vi.作为因素', '1. The determinate factor of our economy is to control inflation. 我们经济的决定性因素是控制通货膨胀。 2. The committee\'s support is an important factor in the success of the project. 委员会的支持是该项目取得成功的一个重要因素。 3. 2, 3, 4 and 6 are factors of 12. 2、3、4 和6是12的因子。 4. A new factor appears under the integral sign. 积分号内出现了一个新的因子。', '形容词: factorable 名词: factorship 过去式: factored 过去分词: factored 现在分词: factoring 第三人称单数: factors');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('robust', '[roʊ\'bʌst]', 'adj.强健的；稳固的；耐用的；粗野的；浓的', '1. She was almost 90, but still very robust. 她将近90岁了，但身体仍然十分强健。 2. But I can say for sure that our monetary system is robust. 但是,我可以很肯定地讲,我们的货币体系是稳固。 3. He bought a robust metal cabinet for his new house. 他为新家购置了一个坚固耐用的金属柜。 4. He is a man with a rather robust sense of humor. 他具备颇为粗俗的幽默感。', '副词: robustly 名词: robustness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suit', '[suːt]', 'n.套装；诉讼；请求 v.适合；方便；满足', '1. It is the convention for men to wear suits on formal occasions. 男子在正式场合穿套装是一种社会习俗。 2. He was dressed in a quiet grey suit and looked very well bred and every inch a gentleman. 他身着素灰色套装，看上去很有涵养，一副绅士派头。 3. She filed a suit against the college for sex discrimination. 她对那所大学提出性别歧视的诉讼。 4. I do not know the first thing about the law suit. 我一点儿也知道这件诉讼案的事。 5. I don\'t know what profession would suit me. 我不知道什么职业适合我干。', '过去式: suited 过去分词: suited 现在分词: suiting 第三人称单数: suits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('arouse', '[ə\'raʊz]', 'v.叫醒；唤醒；激起；睡醒', '1. It took her some time to arouse her husband. 她费了好一会儿才把丈夫叫醒。 2. Diana aroused them just before dawn. 戴安娜在黎明前唤醒了他们。 3. He fell into a sound sleep, don\'t arouse him. 他睡熟了，别唤醒他。 4. The slogan was designd to arouse the people. 该标语是为唤醒国民而拟定的。', '名词: arousal 过去式: aroused 过去分词: aroused 现在分词: arousing 第三人称单数: arouses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('economic', '[ˌiːkə\'nɑːmɪk]', 'adj.经济学的；经济的；有利可图的', '1. Economic analysis displays its effectiveness in tackling pollution. 通过对污染税的经济学分析可以看出其较强的治理效果。 2. They had led the country into economic disaster. 他们把国家带入了经济灾难中。 3. The threat of an economic depression hangs over the world. 经济衰退的威胁笼罩着世界。 4. The economic sanctions could not prevent the development of that country. 经济制裁不能阻碍那个国家的发展。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('stranger', '[\'streɪndʒər]', 'n.陌生人；外地人；新手', '1. A sergeant asked the stranger to show his pass. 警官要求这个陌生人出示通行证。 2. A stranger plucked at my sleeve as I was leaving. 我刚要离去，一个陌生人拽我的袖子。 3. His habitual place at the table was occupied by a stranger. 他惯常坐在桌旁的位置被一个陌生人占据了。 4. It\'s hard for a stranger to make friends in this town. 外地人在这个城里很难交朋友。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('suck', '[sʌk]', 'vt.啜；吸入；吸收 vi.吸；吸收；奉承；<俚>烂 n.吸吮；吸力', '1. Don\'t suck your thumb; it\'s so dirty. 别舔手指头，太脏了。 2. They suck soda water through straws. 他们用吸管喝汽水。 3. Plants suck water from the ground. 植物从地中吸收水分。 4. They use their tongues to suck in the green food. 它们用舌头吮吸着绿色食品。 5. She had a suck of orange juice. 她吸了一口橘子汁。', '过去式: sucked 过去分词: sucked 现在分词: sucking 第三人称单数: sucks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skate', '[skeɪt]', 'v.溜冰；滑冰 n.冰鞋；滑冰', '1. In winter, many people skate on the lake. 冬天时，许多人在湖上溜冰。 2. The ice is too thin to skate on. 冰太薄,不能在上面溜冰。 3. The Dutch often skate along the canals in winter. 冬天荷兰人经常沿着运河滑冰。 4. I can move very fast across the ice on skates. 我穿着冰鞋在冰上滑得很快。', '过去式: skated 过去分词: skated 现在分词: skating 第三人称单数: skates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accommodate', '[ə\'kɑːmədeɪt]', 'vt.供给住宿；使适应；容纳；提供；顾及；调解 vi.适应；调节', '1. This hotel can accommodate up to 500 guests. 这旅馆可供500位来宾住宿。 2. We must accommodate ourselves to circumstances. 我们必须适应环境。 3. One flat can accommodate a family of five. 一套单元房可容纳一个五口之家。 4. The bank is accommodating its customers more than it used to. 这家银行现在给客户贷款比以前多了。 5. Her eyes took a while to accommodate to the darkness. 过了一会儿，她的眼睛才能适应黑暗。', '形容词: accommodative 名词: accommodativeness 过去式: accommodated 过去分词: accommodated 现在分词: accommodating 第三人称单数: accommodates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('scrap', '[skræp]', 'n.碎片；废品；少许；瘦小的人；争斗；打架 v.报废；舍弃；打架', '1. They wrote messages to each other on scraps of paper. 他们用一些碎纸片互传信息。 2. The cars have been broken down for scraps. 那些汽车已经拆掉当废铁。 3. It won\'t make a scrap of difference. 这不会有丝毫的差别。 4. There is not a scrap of truth in what he has said. 他说的话没有半点是真的。 5. I\'ll soon have to scrap this lawn mower,it\'s beyond repair and on its last legs. 不久将不得不把我这台割草机废弃掉，因它已不能修理，即将报废了。', '名词: scrapper 过去式: scrapped 过去分词: scrapped 现在分词: scrapping 第三人称单数: scraps');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('radiate', '[\'reɪdieɪt]', 'v.放射；散发；辐射；流露', '1. Eight roads radiate from the square. 八条大道从广场呈辐射形伸展出去。 2. Heat radiated from the stove. 炉子散发的热量。 3. Heat radiates from the heating radiator and spreads to every corner of the room. 热从暖气片散发出来并传播到室内各个角落。 4. The radiance of electric lights radiates from the ceiling. 电灯的光芒从天花板上辐射下来。', '形容词: radiative 过去式: radiated 过去分词: radiated 现在分词: radiating 第三人称单数: radiates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('bin', '[bɪn]', 'n.箱柜；仓；垃圾箱 vt.放入箱内', '1. They\'re putting them into a white bin. 他们把它们放进一个白色的箱柜里。 2. I bought a bread bin for my family. 我给家里买了一个面包箱。 3. Chuck it in the bin! 把它扔到垃圾桶里去！ 4. Please put all your sweet wrappers in the bin. 请把你们的糖纸都放进垃圾箱里去。 5. Do you need to keep these letters or shall we bin them? 你需要保存这些信件吗，还是干脆把它们扔掉?', '过去式: binned 过去分词: binned 现在分词: binning 第三人称单数: bins');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('transmit', '[træns\'mɪt]', 'vt.传达；传染；传送；代代相传 vi.(以无线电或有线电的方式)发送信号', '1. Gypsies frequently transmit recipes orally within the family. 吉普赛人经常以口头形式把秘方世代相传。 2. Please transmit my best regards to your lovely wife. 请转达我向您娇妻的致意。 3. This infection is transmitted by mosquitoes. 这种传染病是由蚊子传染的。 4. The tension soon transmitted itself to all the members of the crowd. 这种紧张情绪很快感染了人群中所有的人。', '形容词: transmittable 过去式: transmitted 过去分词: transmitted 现在分词: transmitting 第三人称单数: transmits');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('wild', '[waɪld]', 'adj.野生的；野蛮的；未开发的；狂热的 adv.胡乱地；失去控制地 n.荒野；荒地', '1. In nature, all animals are wild and free. 在自然界，一切动物都是野生的，自由自在的。 2. North America has the world\'s best climate for wild grapes. 北美的气候是世界上最适合野生葡萄生长的。 3. I was living like a wild child. 我的行为像个野蛮的孩子。 4. Nothing is sacred to these wild youths. 这些狂野的年轻人什么都不尊重。 5. You can\'t make wild accusations like that! 你不能这样胡乱地指责别人。 6. Danger in the wild comes from the carnivores. 荒野地带的危险来自食肉动物。', '副词: wildly 比较级: wilder 最高级: wildest 名词: wildness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('liberal', '[\'lɪbərəl]', 'adj.慷慨的；大方的；开明的；自由主义的 n.自由主义者；开明的人', '1. They are liberal in their help. 他们慷慨相助。 2. She is liberal with her money. 她用钱大方。 3. Her parents are very liberal and allow her a lot of freedom. 她的父母很开明，让她享有许多的自由。 4. The headmaster has liberal views about what his pupils should wear. 校长对他的学生应穿什么服装这一点持开明的态度。 5. He is an open-minded liberal. 他是一个开明的自由主义者。', '副词: liberally 名词: liberalness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('layer', '[\'ler]', 'n.层 vi.分层 vt.将某物堆积成层', '1. This layer of rock contains a lot of flint. 这一岩层中有大量燧石。 2. There is a fine layer of dust on the desk. 桌子上有一层薄薄的尘土。 3. There are several layers of meaning. 有几层不同的含意。 4. The pollution had destroyed ozone layer and caused many changes in weather. 污染破坏了臭氧层，并引起了许多天气变化。 5. Mists layered thick about him. 层层雾霭笼罩着他。 6. Layer the potatoes and onions in a dish. 把土豆和洋葱分层放在盘子里。', '过去式: layered 过去分词: layered 现在分词: layering 第三人称单数: layers');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('pest', '[pest]', 'n.害虫；讨厌的人', '1. Stores of grain are frequently attacked by pests. 储存的谷物经常受到害虫的破坏。 2. It won\'t be long before we can be rid of the pest altogether. 不要太久，我们就能把这种害虫消除干净。 3. That child is being a real pest. 那个孩子真讨厌。 4. My little brother is a pest when he spoils my games. 我的小弟弟破坏我的各种游戏真讨厌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('legitimate', '[lɪ\'dʒɪtɪmət]', 'adj.合法的；世袭的；婚生的；正当的；合理的 vt.使合法；授权；宣布 ... 为合法', '1. I\'m not sure that his business is strictly legitimate. 我说不好他的生意是否全部合法。 2. He is a legitimate heir to the throne. 他是王位的合法继承人。 3. a legitimate son. 婚生子 4. Politicians are legitimate targets for satire. 政治家理所当然是讽刺的靶子。 5. Distributed Denial of Service, which depletes the network\'s resource and denies service to legitimate users, is one of the hardest security problems in the Internet. 分布式拒绝服务攻击，目的在于耗尽网络资源从而使合法用户的服务请求被拒绝，是最难解决的网络安全问题之一。', '副词: legitimately 名词: legitimateness 过去式: legitimated 过去分词: legitimated 现在分词: legitimating 第三人称单数: legitimates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('detective', '[dɪ\'tektɪv]', 'n.侦探 adj.侦探的', '1. The detective laid great stress on details. 侦探特别强调细节。 2. The detective was trying to ascertain exactly who was at the party. 这个侦探试图查明都有谁参加了聚会。 3. The detective thought the stick was relative to the murder case. 侦探认为这根木棒和谋杀案有牵连。 4. The detective tried to reason out how the thief had escaped. 这个侦探反复琢磨想弄明白那个窃贼是怎样逃跑的。 5. She read detective stories as an escape. 她看侦探小说解闷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('oath', '[oʊθ]', 'n.誓言；誓约；咒骂语', '1. Repeat the oath after me. 请跟着我宣誓。 2. The judge received their oath of allegiance. 法官听取了他们的忠诚誓言。 3. Tom stood by his oath to his father. 汤姆遵守他给父亲立下的誓言。 4. She carries an oath rod that will destory the minds of those it strikes. 她携带着一根誓约之杖，能够摧毁所有被杖击中者的意识。', '名词复数: oaths');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('only', '[\'oʊnli]', 'adv.只有；仅仅；刚刚 adj.最好的；唯一的；出众的 conj.但是；除非；然而；毕竟', '1. This colt is only two months old. 这只小雄驹只有两个月大。 2. He had only a few coppers with him. 他身边只有几枚铜币。 3. You\'re only a child in his eyes. 在他眼里你仅仅是个孩子。 4. This is only an exercise in composition. 这仅仅是一篇习作。 5. She says Italy is the only place to go for a holiday. 她说意大利是度假的最隹去处。 6. The book is likely to be useful, only it\'s rather expensive. 这本书可能有用，只是相当贵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('concise', '[kən\'saɪs]', 'adj.简明的；简要的', '1. His article is concise and comprehensive. 他的文章言简意赅。 2. I like the new concise dictionary very much. 我很喜欢这部新的简明词典。 3. I gave a concise answer to this. 我对于此事给了一个简要的答复。 4. He gave a concise and firm summary of our position. 他扼要而坚定地阐述了我方的立场。', '副词: concisely 名词: conciseness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('intelligible', '[ɪn\'telɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.可理解的；明白易懂的；清楚的', '1. His theory is not intelligible to us. 他的理论我们无法理解。 2. The book is intelligible to anyone. 这本书任何人都看得懂。 3. The answers must be intelligible, but they do not have to be in complete sentences. 答案必须要清楚明晰，不过不必是完整的句子。', '副词: intelligibly 名词: intelligibility');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('passenger', '[\'pæsɪndʒər]', 'n.乘客；旅客', '1. The mysterious woman passenger vanished. 这位神秘的女乘客突然不见了。 2. The passenger berthed beside me. 这名乘客的铺位在我的旁边。 3. The allowance per passenger is 25 kg. 每个旅客的行李重量限25公斤。 4. Passenger traffic has gone up by 20 per cent. 客流量已增长百分之二十。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('poke', '[poʊk]', 'n.戳；刺；拨；钱袋 v.戳；捅；刺；拨开；伸出', '1. In his view, a pinch, a whack or a poke essentially tugged on a neural rope that then rang a pain alarm bell in the brain. 他的看法是，无论是捏、打或戳的动作，基本上都拉动了某根神经索，而敲响脑中某个疼痛的警铃。 2. I didn\'t know Haku had a fast poke. 我还不知道白有快速刺拳这一手。 3. He used a nail to poke a hole. 他用钉子刺了个洞。 4. At frequent intervals the driver used to stop, poke the fire and add fresh fuel. 在经常性的间歇中，司机常常停下来拨一下火，加上新的汽油。 5. Don\'t poke her eye out with that stick! 别让那根棍子戳着她的眼！', '过去式: poked 过去分词: poked 现在分词: poking 第三人称单数: pokes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('billion', '[\'bɪljən]', 'n.十亿', '1. It took them more than one billion dollars to complete the project. 完成这个工程花费了他们十亿多美元。 2. Some computers can perform over a billion computation a second. 有些计算机一秒钟能完成超过十亿次运算。 3. The human brain contains several billion nerve cells, which are connected with one another by fine nerves. 人类的大脑含有几十亿个神经细胞，这些细胞由纤细的神经将彼此连接起来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('interval', '[\'ɪntərvl]', 'n.间隔；休息时间；(数学)区间；(音乐)音程', '1. He comes back to see us at regular intervals. 他每隔一段时间就回来看看我们。 2. The proper intervals should be maintained between vehicles. 车辆之间应保持适当的间距。 3. The performance runs 2 hours 30 minutes including an interval. 整个演出2小时30分,包括中间休息。 4. These equations are interval linear equations. 该控制方程是线性区间方程组。', '形容词: intervalic');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('repair', '[rɪ\'per]', 'v.修理；修补；补救；赴；去 n.修理；修补；补救；维修工作；维修状态', '1. She turned the chair on its side to repair it. 她把椅子翻转过来修理。 2. I\'ll have my watch repaired; it doesn\'t work. 我得修修表，它不走了。 3. The overcoat is so old, it won\'t repair. 这件大衣太旧了，不能修补了。 4. How can I repair the wrong I have done her? 我冤枉了她，怎样才能补救呢？ 5. The brickwork in this house is in need of repair. 这所房子的砖造需要修理。', '形容词: repairable 副词: repairably 名词: repairability 过去式: repaired 过去分词: repaired 现在分词: repairing 第三人称单数: repairs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('saw', '[sɔː]', 'n.锯 v.用锯子锯；前后移动；看见，明白，了解（动词see的过去式）', '1. The electric saw whined as it cut the wood. 电锯在锯木头时嘎嘎作响。 2. You need a powerful saw to cut through metal. 切割金属需用强劲的锯。 3. They are sawing a log into planks. 他们把原木锯成一块块厚板。 4. She tried to saw off a dead branch from the tree. 她试图把那棵树上的一截枯枝锯掉。', '名词: sawer 过去式: sawed 过去分词: sawed/sawn 现在分词: sawing 第三人称单数: saws');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('admire', '[əd\'maɪər]', 'vt.钦佩；赞美；羡慕；欣赏', '1. You may not like him, but you have got to admire his persistence. 你可以不喜欢他，但你不得不佩服他那种坚韧不拔的精神。 2. We admire him for his righteousness. 我们钦佩他的正直。 3. You had better admire others more than criticize if you want to be popular. 如果你想要更受人欢迎,尽量多赞美、少批评。 4. Visitors admire Beijing for its beauty. 观光者赞赏北京的美丽。', '副词: admiringly 名词: admirer 过去式: admired 过去分词: admired 现在分词: admiring 第三人称单数: admires');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('industrial', '[ɪn\'dʌstriəl]', 'adj.工业的；产业的 n.工业公司', '1. She is an industrial designer. 她是工业设计师。 2. The industrial exposition will be held on September. 工业博览会将于九月召开。 3. The industrial revolution had taken place in England first. 工业革命首先在英国发生。 4. Due to low investment, our industrial output has remained stagnant. 由于投资少，我们的工业生产一直停滞不前。 5. He troubleshoots for a large industrial firm. 他受雇为一家大工业公司检修故障。', '副词: industrially');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('literacy', '[\'lɪtərəsi]', 'n.识字；读写能力；文化，教养', '1. I can\'t believe that he failed the literacy test. 我无法相信他识字测试不及格。 2. Mass literacy was only possible after the invention of printing. 发明了印刷术后文化教育才得以普及。 3. Literacy may not be an inalienable human right. 能读写可能算不得是一项不可剥夺的人权。 4. Literacy was not the lecturers\' only concern. 大学讲师所担心的不仅是读写能力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('analysis', '[ə\'næləsɪs]', 'n.分析；解析', '1. His analysis of the problem showed great perception. 他对该问题的分析显示出敏锐的洞察力。 2. We agreed with his acute analysis of the political situation. 我们都同意他对政治形势的深刻分析。 3. Close analysis of sales figures showed clear regional variations. 对销售额的仔细分析显示出明显的地区差别。 4. In the final analysis I think our sympathy lies with the heroine of the play. 总之，我们认为我们都同情剧中的女主人公。', '名词复数: analyses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('corrode', '[kə\'roʊd]', 'v.腐蚀；侵蚀；损害', '1. Iron corrodes easily. 铁易锈损。 2. This acid may corrode iron. 这种酸能腐蚀铁。 3. Certain chemicals will corrode if left on bare metal. 有些化学药品如留在裸露的金属上会起腐蚀作用。 4. The furniture should be of smooth, hard material not liable to warp or corrode. 家具应使用光滑、坚硬、不易变形和腐蚀的材料制作。', '形容词: corrodible 过去式: corroded 过去分词: corroded 现在分词: corroding 第三人称单数: corrodes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('objective', '[əb\'dʒektɪv]', 'adj.客观的；真实的；宾语的 n.目标；目的；[物]物镜；[语]宾语', '1. From any objective perspective,it is simply too long. 从客观的角度来讲，这实在是太长了。 2. She gives an objective report of what has happened. 她就发生的事情进行客观的报告。 3. He has told a story which sound not objective. 他讲了听起来不真实的一个故事。 4. Her principal objective was international fame as a scientist. 她的主要目标是当个有国际声誉的科学家。', '副词: objectively 名词: objectiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('freight', '[freɪt]', 'n.（货运）运费；货运；货物 vt.装货于；运送', '1. At an auction, the buyer pays the freight. 在拍卖会上，买家支付运费。 2. The freight must be added to the cost of the goods. 运费必须打入货的成本。 3. We can send it by air/sea freight. 我们可以空运[海运]。 4. Eight thousand tons of freight were being landed each day. 每天卸货8000吨上岸。 5. They freighted the boat with bananas. 他们把香蕉装上船。', '过去式: freighted 过去分词: freighted 现在分词: freighting 第三人称单数: freights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('whatever', '[wət\'evər]', 'pron.无论什么；任何事物 adj.不管怎样的；所有的；丝毫的', '1. We shall remain friends whatever may betide. 无论发生什么事，我们将永远是朋友。 2. Whatever nonsense the papers print, some people always believe it. 不管报纸胡说什么,总有一些人信以为真。 3. Whatever requests you make will be granted. 你提的任何请求都会得到许可 4. She applied whatever strength she had left to the task. 她将所有剩下的精力都用到这项任务上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('input', '[\'ɪnpʊt]', 'n.投入；输入信息；输入数据；信息输入端 v.输入', '1. I\'d appreciate your input on this. 我将感激你在这方面的投入。 2. The input was larger than the output, so they lost money. 投入大于产出,所以他们亏本了。 3. The state has further increased its input in the family planning undertaking. 国家进一步加大了对计划生育事业的投入。 4. There are several errors in the input. 输入中有好几处错误。 5. I have inputted the data into a computer. 我已经把数据输入到计算机中了。', '过去式: inputted/input 过去分词: inputted/input 现在分词: inputting 第三人称单数: inputs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('straight', '[streɪt]', 'adj.直的；坦率的；正直的；准的；连续的；异性恋的 adv.笔直地；直接；坦率地；连续不断地 n.直的东西；传统的人；异性恋者', '1. Light travels in straight lines. 光是沿直线传播。 2. I want a straight answer to the question. 我想提问和回答都要直截了当。 3. John Wayne was a blunt talker and straight shooter. 约翰·韦恩是一个直言不讳、一针见血的人。 4. He is as straight as an arrow. 他是个正直的人。 5. The smoke rose straight up. 烟直直地上升。', '副词: straightly 比较级: straighter 最高级: straightest 名词: straightness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('manager', '[\'mænɪdʒər]', 'n.经理；管理者；管家', '1. The manager let us cut the cackle. 经理让我们不要闲谈。 2. I want to speak to the sales manager. 我想找营业部经理。 3. He is the manager of the warehouse. 他是这个仓库的管理者。 4. You could talk with the related manager of the school about the issue. 你可以和学校相关管理人员说说这事。', '名词: managership');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('minute', '[\'mɪnɪt]', 'n.分钟；片刻；备忘；会议记录 adj.微小的；仔细的 vt.记录', '1. The park is only five minutes from downtown. 这个花园离市中心只有五分钟的路程。 2. Please wait a minute, I\'ll go with you right now. 请等一下,我马上跟你走。 3. She has the habit of making a minute of daily businesses. 她有记录每天各种事务的习惯。 4. He took down the minutes in shorthand. 他将会议记录速记下来。 5. I remembered in minute detail everything that had happened. 我对发生的每件事的细枝末节都记得清清楚楚。 6. Have you minuted what I have just said? 你记下我刚刚说的话了吗？', '名词: minuteness 过去式: minuted 过去分词: minuted 现在分词: minuting 第三人称单数: minutes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('song', '[sɔːŋ]', 'n.歌曲；歌唱；(鸟等)鸣声', '1. The song has plaintive melody. 这首歌曲的曲调悲伤。 2. I woke up and was greeted by bird song. 我一觉醒来，鸟鸣之声不绝于耳。 3. The song of birds heralds spring. 鸟儿的歌唱预报春到。 4. He was awakened by the song of birds in the trees. 他被林中的鸟鸣声闹醒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('place', '[pleɪs]', 'n.地方；地位；职位；获奖的名次 v.将（某物）放置；安排；订货；寄托；辨认；获得名次', '1. We must find a place for this new picture. 我们必须找一个地方放这张新照片。 2. Put everything away in its correct place. 把东西放到该放的地方去。 3. Social science affirms that a woman\'s place in society marks the level of civilization. 社会科学认为,妇女在社会里的地位标志着文明的水平。 4. Geoffrey Chaucer occupies a unique place in English literature . 杰弗里·乔叟在英国文学中占有独一无二的地位。 5. He placed the books in order on the shelf. 他把书按顺序摆在书架上.', '形容词: placeable 名词: placer 过去式: placed 过去分词: placed 现在分词: placing 第三人称单数: places');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('people', '[\'piːpl]', 'n.人；人民；人们 v.使住人；居住于', '1. Were there many people at the meeting? 集会有很多人吗？ 2. People become uninhibited when they drink. 人一喝酒就会变得肆无忌惮。 3. I think it my duty to serve the people. 我认为为人民服务是我的责任。 4. He expresses sympathy for the working people. 他表现了对劳动人民的同情。 5. Hunters peopled these forests long ago. 猎人们很久以前就住在这片森林里。', '名词: peopler 名词复数: people 过去式: peopled 过去分词: peopled 现在分词: peopling 第三人称单数: peoples');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('plough', '[plaʊ]', 'v.用犁耕田；耕犁；开(路) n.犁；耕地；铲雪机', '1. Peasants can only plough the land plot by plot. 农民犁田只能一块一块地犁。 2. The ground was ploughed and planted with corn. 地翻耕后种上了玉米。 3. We have to plough out the weeds. 我们得犁掉杂草。 4. The tractors will plough on throughout the night. 拖拉机整个晚上都在犁地。 5. The farmer is at the plough. 那个农民在种田。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('misunderstand', '[ˌmɪsʌndər\'stænd]', 'v.误解；误会；不了解', '1. They pretend to misunderstand my complaint. 他们假装误解了我的投诉。 2. His remarks show that he misunderstood my position on the question. 他的话说明他误解了我在这一问题上的立场。 3. He wrote her a letter for fear she misunderstand him. 他给她写了封信，免得她误会。 4. I think the couple misunderstand each other. 我认为这对夫妇未能真正互相了解。', '过去式: misunderstood 过去分词: misunderstood 现在分词: misunderstanding 第三人称单数: misunderstands');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dock', '[dɑːk]', 'n.码头；船坞；船埠 v.进(港、码头)', '1. The ship\'s hull scraped along the side of the dock. 船行时船身擦着码头的边。 2. The cruise ship is strikebound in the dock. 巡洋舰因罢工而停泊在码头上。 3. The liner is in dock for a refit. 班轮正在船坞修理。 4. The yacht is lying up in the dock. 那条游艇正停在船坞里。 5. He rowed up the canal looking for a place to dock the boat. 他在运河里划船，寻找一个码头泊船。', '过去式: docked 过去分词: docked 现在分词: docking 第三人称单数: docks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('ambition', '[æm\'bɪʃn]', 'n.雄心；抱负；野心；精力 vt.追求；有 ... 野心', '1. You should persist in your ambition. 你应该坚持你的雄心大志。 2. The glory of his country is his ambition. 为国增光是他的雄心。 3. You will achieve your ambition if you work hard. 如果你努力, 你的抱负是可以实现的。 4. That political statesman is full of ambition. 那个政治家野心很大。 5. I never ambitioned it. 我从来不妄想得到它。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('outlook', '[\'aʊtlʊk]', 'n.景色；前景；展望；观点', '1. The house has a pleasant outlook over the valley. 从这所房子可以看到山谷景色优美。 2. From my study window I have a pleasant outlook over mountains and valleys. 从我书房的窗子我看到了高山和峡谷宜人的景色。 3. I am optimistic about the outlook of our country. 我对我们国家的前景持乐观态度。 4. As prices have dropped lower and lower, the outlook looks black for many companies in the city. 当价格一再下跌，对市内许多公司来说前景大为不妙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('spoon', '[spuːn]', 'n.匙；调羹；匙状物 vt.以匙舀起 vi.调情', '1. The spoon has been rusty from disuse. 汤匙因弃置不用而生锈了。 2. His soup spoon dropped onto the ground. 他的汤勺掉到了地上。 3. She was born with a silver spoon in her mouth. 她生来富贵。 4. You need a spoon to beat the mixture smooth. 你需要用一把调羹来搅均混合液。 5. He spooned up several cakes of cube sugar and stuffed them into his mouth. 他舀起了几块方糖,然后把它们全都塞进了嘴里。 6. The young couple spoon all the time. 一对年轻人,常在调情求爱。', '形容词: spoonable 过去式: spooned 过去分词: spooned 现在分词: spooning 第三人称单数: spoons');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('soft', '[sɔːft]', 'adj.柔软的；柔和的；温和的；不强烈的；轻的 adv.柔软地；温和地 n.柔软的东西', '1. The new leaves in springtime have a soft touch. 春天的新芽有柔软的触感。 2. It\'s very comfortable to step on the soft ground in the spring. 春天的时候，踩在松软的地面上非常舒服。 3. The room was flooded with soft light. 房间里充满了柔和的光。 4. The soft breeze stirs the leaves. 柔和的微风摇动着树叶。 5. He comforted his back with something soft. 他用柔软的东西使他的背部舒服一点。', '副词: softly 比较级: softer 最高级: softest 名词: softness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('redundant', '[rɪ\'dʌndənt]', 'adj.多余的，过多的；累赘的，冗长的；解雇的；重复的，千篇一律的', '1. Skill has been made redundant by machine. 由于使用机器，手艺已变得多余。 2. This word is redundant, it can be left out. 这个字是多余的, 可以去掉。 3. There are too many redundant words in this book. 这本书里多余的词太多。', '副词: redundantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shove', '[ʃʌv]', 'v.推挤；撞；乱塞；乱放 n.推；挤', '1. Don\'t try to shove all the work onto me! 别把工作都推给我！ 2. He dragged her out of the door and shoved her into the street. 他把她拖到门口，猛地把她推到马路上。 3. Then suddenly, Old Grizzly gave Brown Bear a big shove. 突然间，老灰熊给棕色熊一个重重的推撞。 4. Bunt was probably a nickname given to him at school, for going around with his head lowered, ready to bump and shove anybody aside. 铁头可能是他上学时得的绰号，那时他总低着头走路，一副准备随时一头把人撞到一边的架势。 5. The car won\'t start. Can you give it a shove? 这车子启动不了。你能不能推它一把?', '名词: shover 过去式: shoved 过去分词: shoved 现在分词: shoving 第三人称单数: shoves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('symbol', '[\'sɪmbl]', 'n.符号；象征；标志', '1. The chemical symbol for copper is \"Cu\". 铜的化学符号是Cu。 2. The dove is the symbol of peace. 鸽子是和平的象征。 3. The river-sea dividing marker must be a symbol which separates the Yalu River from the Yellow Sea. 江海分界碑,这里就是鸭绿江和黄海分界的标志吧。', '过去式: symboled 过去分词: symboled 现在分词: symboling 第三人称单数: symbols');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('calculate', '[\'kælkjuleɪt]', 'v.计算；估计；考虑；推测；计划；指望', '1. I will calculate your bill for you. 我帮您计算账单。 2. Can you calculate the content of the tube? 你能计算出试管的容量吗? 3. Scientists have calculated that the world\'s population will double by the end of the century. 科学家已推算出世界人口在本世纪末将要增加一倍。 4. I calculate it\'s a waste of time to do that. 我想做那件事简直是在浪费时间。', '过去式: calculated 过去分词: calculated 现在分词: calculating 第三人称单数: calculates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('shrug', '[ʃrʌɡ]', 'n.耸肩 v.耸肩；不理会', '1. She gave a shrug of her shoulders. 她耸了耸肩膀。 2. She gave a shrug and walked away. 她耸了耸肩就离开了。 3. I would answer with a shrug of my shoulders. 我总是耸耸肩回答。 4. They would shrug their shoulders, and treat you like a child. 他们一定会耸耸肩膀,把你当作孩子看待!', '过去式: shrugged 过去分词: shrugged 现在分词: shrugging 第三人称单数: shrugs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('injure', '[\'ɪndʒər]', 'vt.伤害；损害；损伤', '1. Don\'t injure yourself with that tool. 不要让那工具伤害到你。 2. He that spare the bad injure the good. 饶恕了恶人，伤害了好人。 3. It would naturally injure him in her estimation. 那自然也会损害到她对他的评价。 4. This rough life threatened to injure his health,but he didn\'t mind. 这种艰苦生活看来要损害他的健康，但他并不介意。', '名词: injurer 过去式: injured 过去分词: injured 现在分词: injuring 第三人称单数: injures');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fertile', '[\'fɜːrtl]', 'adj.肥沃的；富饶的；能繁殖的；多产的；（创造力）丰富的', '1. There are fertile fields in the Nile Delta. 尼罗河三角洲土地肥沃。 2. We have irrigated the desert area to make it fertile. 我们已经灌溉了荒芜地区使它肥沃。 3. It was a pleasant fertile spot, well wooded and rich in pasture. 那是一个富饶的，使人愉快的地方，材木苍然，牧草丰富。 4. This fertile land bears the hopes of the farmers. 这块富饶的土地,孕育着庄稼人的希望！', '副词: fertilely 名词: fertileness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('fascinate', '[\'fæsɪneɪt]', 'vt.使 ... 入迷；吸引住 vi.有吸引力', '1. Anything to do with old myths and legends fascinates me. 任何与上古神话传说有关的东西都会使我着迷。 2. The place continues to fascinate visitors, cloaked in its mystery. 这个地方笼罩在神秘气氛下，继续使游览者着迷。 3. The students were fascinated by his ideas. 学生们都被他的思想吸引住了。 4. I watched her, fascianted. 我瞧着她,完全被她吸引住了。 5. It seems that the private lives of movie stars never fail to fascinate. 电影明星的私生活似乎总是使人津津乐道。', '过去式: fascinated 过去分词: fascinated 现在分词: fascinating 第三人称单数: fascinates');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('theme', '[θiːm]', 'n.主题；题目；主旋律', '1. Peace was the dominant theme of the conference. 和平是大会的首要议题。 2. What is the essential theme of the play? 这剧本的主题是什麽? 3. The theme for tonight\'s talk is education. 今天谈话的题目是教育。 4. The theme of our discussion was Europe in the 1980\'s\'. 我们讨论的题目是｀八十年代的欧洲＇.', '形容词: themeless');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('prime', '[praɪm]', 'adj.最好的；首要的；典型的 n.壮年；全盛时期；青春 n.[数]质数 vt.事先指点；在（金属、木材等上）打底漆 vi.变得首要', '1. He reached his prime and then, when he had the most to live for, he died. 他到了壮年时期,该做出最大贡献,活得最好的时候,却死掉了。 2. We were well prime for the journey with a large breakfast. 为了去旅行,我们早餐都吃得饱饱的。 3. What was said was of prime importance. 说过的那件事是很重要的。 4. Britain has a queen, but it is the prime minister and the cabinet who govern. 英国有女王,但执政的是首相和内阁。 5. He died in the prime of his life. 他在壮年时死去。 6. It states that every even number greater than two can be expressed as the sum of two primes (a prime is a number that is only divisible by itself and by 1, such as 7 and 13). 其陈述是：每一个大于2的偶数都可以表达成两个素数之和(素数是指只能被1和它本身整除的数，如7和13)。 7. She has been well primed about what to say. 她已经有人指点,知道要说些什么。 8. Peace is the prime objective of our foreign policy. 我们把争取和平作为对外政策的首要任务。', '副词: primely 名词: primeness 过去式: primed 过去分词: primed 现在分词: priming 第三人称单数: primes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sale', '[seɪl]', 'n.出售；促销', '1. This is a showpiece, not for sale. 这是个样品,不出售。 2. The law forbids the sale of alcohol to people under 18. 法律禁止向18岁以下的人出售含有酒精的饮料。 3. The local dress shop is having a sale. 附近的时装店正在大拍卖。 4. Is this shampoo on sale today? 这种洗发水今天减价出售吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('affirm', '[ə\'fɜːrm]', 'vt.证实；断言；肯定', '1. Scientists cannot affirm the existence of life on other planets. 科学家们还不能证实在其它星球上有生命存在。 2. I affirm that what he said is true. 我断言他所说的是实情。 3. They affirmed that the girl did quite a bit of reading. 他们断言这个女孩子读了不少书。 4. I can affirm that no one will lose their job. 我可以肯定，谁都不会丢掉工作。', '形容词: affirmable 副词: affirmably 名词: affirmer 过去式: affirmed 过去分词: affirmed 现在分词: affirming 第三人称单数: affirms');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('waken', '[\'weɪkən]', 'v.唤醒；醒来；觉醒；激发', '1. Nature seems to be wakened from a deep sleep. 大自然好像从沉睡中被唤醒。 2. I was wakened by the telephone. 我被电话铃吵醒了。 3. It wakened the local government to realize the need for safety precautions. 这让当地政府觉醒了，认识到必须采取安全预防措施。 4. The dream wakened a forgotten memory. 那梦唤起了一段忘却的记忆。', '名词: wakener 过去式: wakened 过去分词: wakened 现在分词: wakening 第三人称单数: wakens');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('contact', '[\'kɑːntækt]', 'n.接触；联系；熟人 v.(与)联系；(与)接触 adj.接触的', '1. The rich secluded themselves from contact with the poor. 富人不肯同穷人接触。 2. I finally made contact with her in Paris. 我终于在巴黎同她取得了联系。 3. She has a contact in the software industry. 她在软件行业有个熟人。 4. Contact the police at once! 立刻与警方联系！ 5. She suffers from a contact skin rash. 她患上了一种接触传染性皮疹。', '形容词: contactual 副词: contactually 过去式: contacted 过去分词: contacted 现在分词: contacting 第三人称单数: contacts');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('instantaneous', '[ˌɪnstən\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.瞬间的；即刻的', '1. Relief was instantaneous. 痛苦的消除是瞬间的事 2. Death is instantaneous in a fatal accident. 在致命的事故中，死亡是即刻发生的。 3. The reaction of the audience was instantaneous. 观众即刻有了反应。 4. He had an instantaneous response. 他立刻作了反应。', '副词: instantaneously 名词: instantaneity');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('sofa', '[\'soʊfə]', 'n.沙发', '1. The sofa functions as a bed at night. 这沙发在夜里可以当床。 2. There\'s little spring in this sofa. 这张沙发几乎没什么弹性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('log', '[lɔːɡ]', 'n.原木；圆木；(航海、飞行)日志；(船)计程仪 v.伐木；记入(日志)', '1. They are sawing a log into planks. 他们把原木锯成一块块厚板。 2. My brother is chopping logs for the fire. 我哥哥正在为生火劈柴。 3. A log got in his way as he drove. 一根圆木挡住了他开车的去路。 4. The log twiddled round and round in the river. 那根圆木在河水中转来转去。 5. We\'ll log another section of the area today. 今天我们要砍伐另一部分林区的树木。', '过去式: logged 过去分词: logged 现在分词: logging 第三人称单数: logs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('accomplish', '[ə\'kɑːmplɪʃ]', 'vt.完成；实现', '1. I have accomplished a great deal in the last few months. 在过去几个月里，我完成了相当多的工作。 2. The prediction was literally accomplished. 这个预言确实实现了。 3. The role of a judge is to accomplish fairness. 法官的职责是实现公平。', '形容词: accomplishable 名词: accomplisher 过去式: accomplished 过去分词: accomplished 现在分词: accomplishing 第三人称单数: accomplishes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('skip', '[skɪp]', 'v.跳过；略过；遗漏 n.跳跃；跳读；省略', '1. Lambs skipped in the field. 小羊在田野里跳跃。 2. Let\' s skip over this page and come to page 55. 咱们越过这一页，看第五十五页。 3. I read the whole book without skipping(a page). 我一页不漏地读完了整本书。 4. He gave a skip of joy as he heard the news. 得知这个消息，他高兴地跳了起来。', '形容词: skippable 过去式: skipped 过去分词: skipped 现在分词: skipping 第三人称单数: skips');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('mock', '[mɑːk]', 'v.嘲弄；嘲笑；模仿 n.嘲笑；模仿；戏弄 adj.假的；伪装的；模拟的', '1. He went to church only to mock. 他到教堂去只是为了嘲弄宗教。 2. We should not mock at other people\'s religious beliefs. 我们不应该嘲笑别人的宗教信仰。 3. I have a pet monkey which attempts to mock all my actions. 我养了一只猴子当宠物，它试图模仿我所有的动作。 4. His bully make a mock of all the fine thing he say about kindness to others. 他那恃强欺弱的行为对于他所说的待人友善的漂亮言词是一个嘲弄。 5. She handed him the envelope with mock solemnity. 她装出一副郑重其事的样子，把信封交给他。', '副词: mockingly 名词: mocker 过去式: mocked 过去分词: mocked 现在分词: mocking 第三人称单数: mocks');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('art', '[ɑːrt]', 'n.艺术；美术；技巧；艺术品；人文学科；阴谋 adj.艺术(品)的；美术(品)的', '1. She displayed great ardor for art. 她对艺术表现出极大的热心。 2. She joined the university art society. 她加入了大学里的艺术协会。 3. She has an appreciation of art and music. 她对于美术和音乐有了解。 4. The art of painting is not easy to learn. 画画的技巧是不容易学的。 5. She teaches art history in university. 她在大学里教艺术史。', '名词复数: arts 名词: artist');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('blame', '[bleɪm]', 'vt.责备；把 ... 归咎于 n.责备；过失', '1. The driver was not to blame for the accident. 这次事故怪不着司机。 2. The bank manager was really to blame, though he tried to pin it on a clerk. 真正受责备的应该是银行经理，可是他却想把责任推到一个职员身上。 3. She blamed him for the failure of their marriage. 她把婚姻的触礁归咎於他。 4. They blamed the rise in oil prices for the big increase in inflation. 他们把通货膨胀大幅度增长归咎于石油价格的上涨。 5. We were ready to take the blame for what had happened. 我们准备对所发生的事承担责任。', '名词: blamer 过去式: blamed 过去分词: blamed 现在分词: blaming 第三人称单数: blames');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('repeatedly', '[rɪ\'piːtɪdli]', 'adv.重复地；再三地', '1. And doing it repeatedly would cause damage. 并且重复地这样做会引起毁灭。 2. He drew a long breath and repeatedly chanted the name of Rama, every word showering nectar into the hearts of the devotees. 他深深地吸了一口气，重复地唱颂着罗摩的名字，每一个字都像甘露般地洒落在奉献者的心里。 3. I repeatedly have to suffer the indignity of telling people that I live with my parents. 我再三地忍受到侮辱，告诉他们我现在和我的双亲一起生活。 4. B. However, in order to restore peace and social order, individual states or the international community has repeatedly used force in history. 然而，历史上为了恢复和平和社会秩序，个别的国家或国际社会再三地使用武力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('envisage', '[ɪn\'vɪzɪdʒ]', 'vt.面对；想像', '1. Nobody can envisage the consequences of total nuclear war. 没有人能想像出全面核子战争的后果。 2. I don\'t envisage working with him again. 我想像不出再与他一起工作的可能。 3. Nobody can envisage the consequences of total nuclear war. 没有人能想像出全面核子战争的后果。 4. I can\'t envisage the plan(\'s)working. 我无法设想计划能否行得通.', '过去式: envisaged 过去分词: envisaged 现在分词: envisaging 第三人称单数: envisages');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('boil', '[bɔɪl]', 'v.沸腾；煮沸；激动 n.煮沸；翻滚；疖', '1. The kettle is boiling. 壶里的水开了。 2. I am boiling the milk. 我正在煮牛奶。 3. This new type of electromagnetic boiler takes only 3 minutes to boil water. 这样的新型电磁炉煮沸一锅水只用3分钟。 4. The mere idea made me boil. 这个主意让我大为激动。 5. Give the sheets a good boil to get them white. 把被单好好煮一煮，好让它们白一些。', '过去式: boiled 过去分词: boiled 现在分词: boiling 第三人称单数: boils');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('dissolve', '[dɪ\'zɑːlv]', 'vt.使溶解；解散；消除；解决(问题)；使沮丧 vi.溶解；液化；消散；变得模糊 n.叠化画面', '1. Dissolve one tablet in warm water. 将一片药片溶解在热水中。 2. The parliament was dissolved. 议会解散了。 3. As president, he can dissolve parliament on a whim. 作为总统，他可以随意解散议会。 4. Plasmin is the main protease to break down and dissolve thrombus. 胞浆素是消除和分解血栓的主要蛋白酶。 5. Ice dissolved in the warm weather. 冰在温暖的天气中溶化了。', '形容词: dissolvable 名词: dissolver 过去式: dissolved 过去分词: dissolved 现在分词: dissolving 第三人称单数: dissolves');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('elegant', '[\'elɪɡənt]', 'adj.优雅的；雅致的', '1. He strolled about, looking very debonair in his elegant new suit. 他穿了一身讲究的新衣服逛来逛去，显得颇为惬意。 2. He proudly promenaded his elegant companion in the park. 他得意地领著他那标致的伴侣遛公园。 3. We all wonder how you always look so young and beautiful and elegant! 我们都很想知道,为什么你总是那么优雅年轻。 4. The lady wears an elegant dark suit. 那位女士穿着雅致的深色套装。', '副词: elegantly');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('become', '[bɪ\'kʌm]', 'v.变成；成为；变得；适合（某人）；使（人）显得漂亮', '1. Vast areas of land have become desert. 广大的地区均已变成沙漠。 2. You may also find that reading has become more fun than work! 你或许也会发现阅读已经变成是有趣的事，而不是工作。 3. The entrepreneur has become a news figure. 这位企业家变成了新闻人物。 4. Every one cannot become businessman. 不是所有的人都能成为商人。', '过去式: became 过去分词: become 现在分词: becoming 第三人称单数: becomes');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('comprehend', '[ˌkɑːmprɪ\'hend]', 'vt.充分理解；领悟；包括', '1. I cannot comprehend this phrase. 我无法理解这个片语。 2. If you can use a word correctly and effectively you comprehend it. 你如果可以正确有效地使用一个词，你就是了解它了。 3. The child couldn\'t comprehend the text. 这孩子不懂该课文的含义。 4. The park comprehends all the land on the other side of the river. 这个公园包括河对岸的所有地方。', '形容词: comprehendible 副词: comprehendingly 过去式: comprehended 过去分词: comprehended 现在分词: comprehending 第三人称单数: comprehends');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('yet', '[jet]', 'adv.还；已经；仍然 conj.然而；但是', '1. He hasn\'t done much yet. 他做的还不很多。 2. \"It\'s time to go.\" \"I\'m not ready yet.\" 出路 3. Have you composed your masterpiece yet? Have we seen it? 对你来说,你是否已经完成了你的杰作了呢?我们什么时候能见到它? 4. Edwina nodded, not ready yet to speak. 埃德温娜点点头,仍然呆呆地说不出话来。 5. It was a rash thing to do, yet one cannot but admire her courage. 这事做得过于鲁莽', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('missionary', '[\'mɪʃəneri]', 'n.传教士 adj.传教的', '1. The missionary was sent to India last year. 这名传教士去年被派到印度。 2. He disguised himself as a missionary. 他伪装成传教士。 3. We need to motivate members to do missionary work. 我们必须策励教友传教的工作。 4. Our missionary work had an important breakthrough. 我们的传教工作有了很重要的突破。', '名词复数: missionaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('cheese', '[tʃiːz]', 'n.干酪；乳酪；奶酪 vt.使停止', '1. This cheese is rather bland. 这干酪没什么味道。 2. The cheese was emitting a strong smell. 干酪散发出强烈的气味。 3. Just have a taste of this cheese! 尝一点儿这种乳酪吧！ 4. Cheese often upsets her stomach. 她吃乳酪後常常感到肠胃不适。 5. Cheese it, or you\'ll have the ceiling down. 别吵了，否则天花板就要给你们吵下来了。', '过去式: cheesed 过去分词: cheesed 现在分词: cheesing 第三人称单数: cheeses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('history', '[\'hɪstri]', 'n.历史；历史学；对过去事情的记载；过去的事', '1. The English language has an interesting history. 英语有着饶有趣味的发展历史。 2. China is an oriental country with a long history. 中国是一个有着悠久历史的东方国家。 3. He specializes in oriental history. 他专门研究东方史。 4. He asked a little about my life history. 他简单地问了一下我的履历。', '名词复数: histories');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('trade', '[treɪd]', 'n.贸易；交易；行业；同行；顾客；营业额；交易量 v.做生意；从事贸易；购物；营业；(在证券交易所)交易；交换', '1. China does a lot of trade with many countries. 中国和许多国家进行多方面贸易。 2. There has been some shrinkage in our export trade. 我们的出口贸易量已有些减少。 3. He started his daughter up in the trade. 他让女儿从事这一行业。 4. They offer discounts to the trade(= to people who are working in the same business). 他们对同行业的人给予折扣。 5. I refuse to trade with that company again. 我拒绝再度和那家公司做生意。', '形容词: tradable 过去式: traded 过去分词: traded 现在分词: trading 第三人称单数: trades');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('anywhere', '[\'eniwer]', 'adv.任何地方 n.任何(一个)地方', '1. The city welcomes visitors from anywhere. 这座城市欢迎来自任何地方的来访客人。 2. One day they may be able to go anywhere in space. 会有那么一天，它们也许能够进入太空的任何地方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('courtyard', '[\'kɔːrtjɑːrd]', 'n.庭院；院子', '1. The courtyard was shaded by high trees. 庭院荫庇在大树下。 2. Rise at dawn and sweep the courtyard. 黎明即起，洒扫庭除。 3. The hotel is built round a courtyard, with fountain and palm tree. 这家饭店围绕一庭院而建，辅以泉水和棕榈树。 4. These bricks are to pave the courtyard. 这些砖要用来铺院子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('objection', '[əb\'dʒekʃn]', 'n.反对；异议', '1. I have no objection to their plan. 我不反对他们的计划。 2. None of them raised any objection. 他们谁也没提出反对意见。 3. He has a strong objection to getting up early. 他强烈反对早起。 4. I see no objection whatsoever. 我没有任何异议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('rotary', '[\'roʊtəri]', 'adj.旋转的 n.旋转式机器；环形交叉路', '1. The central unit is a rotary drum. 核心设备是一个旋转的滚筒。 2. The rotary agitator irrigated him. 旋转的鼓动者可灌溉的他。', '名词复数: rotaries');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('inclusive', '[ɪn\'kluːsɪv]', 'adj.包含 ... 在内的；包罗广泛的；包括端点的 [计算机] 包括的', '1. The monthly rent is $20 inclusive of everything. 月房租总共二十美元,包括一切费用在内。 2. His concept of history is modern and inclusive. 她的历史观现代又富包容性。 3. The party must adopt more inclusive strategies and a broader vision. 这个党必须采取更广泛的策略和更远大的视野。 4. I\'ll be away from the 20th to the 31st of May inclusive. 我从五月二十号到三十一号（包括这两天）,都不会在。', '副词: inclusively 名词: inclusiveness');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('collapse', '[kə\'læps]', 'v.（使）倒塌；（使）崩溃；（使）瓦解；折叠 n.倒塌；崩溃；暴跌', '1. The roof collapsed under the weight of snow. 房顶在雪的重压下突然坍塌下来。 2. If you work too hard,your health may collapse. 如果你工作太累的话，你可能病倒。 3. The enterprise collapsed through lack of support. 该企业因无力支持而倒闭。 4. He collapsed the wheelchair and put it on the boat. 他将轮椅折叠起来放在船上。 5. A flood caused the collapse of the bridge. 洪水使桥倒塌了。', '形容词: collapsible 名词: collapsibility 过去式: collapsed 过去分词: collapsed 现在分词: collapsing 第三人称单数: collapses');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('nutrition', '[nu\'trɪʃn]', 'n.营养', '1. Variety is not a guarantee of good nutrition. 品种多并不能确保营养好。 2. This food provides all the nutrition your dog needs. 本食品含有狗所必须的一切营养。 3. A balanced diet provides nutrition for your body. 均衡的食物使你的身体获得营养。', '形容词: nutritional 副词: nutritionally');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('jog', '[dʒɑːɡ]', 'v.慢跑；轻推；（使）颠簸前行 n.慢跑；轻推；颠簸', '1. He goes jogging every night. 他每晚慢跑。 2. You jogged my elbow and spoiled what I was drawing. 你撞到了我的手肘，弄坏了我正在画的图画。 3. The wagon jogged along on the rough road. 马车沿着崎岖不平的道路颠簸前行。 4. I go for a jog in the park every morning. 每天早晨我在公园里慢跑。', '名词: jogger 过去式: jogged 过去分词: jogged 现在分词: jogging 第三人称单数: jogs');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('abatement', '[ə\'beɪtmənt]', 'n.减少；减轻；缓和；减少额；（尤指）减税额', '1. Third, the costs of abatement are large. 第三，减少排放的代价是巨大的。 2. Alstom is a world leader in carbon abatement technologies in the power sector. 他们的技术可以帮助电力行业减少使用含碳的产品。 3. The abatement of the headache gave him a moment of rest. 头痛减轻给他片刻的休息。 4. He couldn\'t make any offers, for that might be pleaded in abatement of what damages a jury might be inclined to give. 他不能出什么主意，因为他们也许会利用他所出的主意来减轻陪审官所定的罚金。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('about', '[ə\'baʊt]', 'prep.关于；大约；在 ... 周围 adv.大约；附近；到处；在周围 adj.即将的；正要的；在流行中的', '1. Tell me all about it. 告诉我关于这件事的一切。 2. It is about six o\'clock now. 现在是六点钟左右。 3. It was a long flight and it took about fourteen hours. 时间真长,飞了大约十四个小时。 4. All about us in the store were piles of goods. 在这家店里,我们周围到处都是成堆的商品。 5. Dinner is about ready. 中饭就要做好了。 6. He was about to start. 他即将动身。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('copyright', '[\'kɑːpiraɪt]', 'n.版权；著作权 v.获得版权 adj.受版权保护的', '1. He decided to resign his claim to the copyright. 他决定放弃对版权的要求。 2. Copyright expires 50 years after the death of the author. 版权在作者死后50年即行终止。 3. He retained the copyright of his book. 他保留此书的著作权。 4. This material is copyright. 本资料享有版权。', '形容词: copyrightable 名词: copyrighter 过去式: copyrighted 过去分词: copyrighted 现在分词: copyrighting 第三人称单数: copyrights');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('death', '[deθ]', 'n.死；死亡；毁灭；死因', '1. The seedling was frozen to death. 幼苗被冻死了。 2. The farm came to him on his father\'s death. 他父亲死时把农场留给他了。 3. The film ends with the death of the heroine. 这部电影以女主角的死告终。 4. Car accidents caused many deaths. 车祸造成很多人死亡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('science', '[\'saɪəns]', 'n.科学；学科；理科；自然科学；专门技巧', '1. She dedicated her life to science. 她毕生致力于科学。 2. Apparently impossible feats are now accomplished by science. 许多看起来不可能的伟大业绩现在已经由科学实现了。 3. He started to study ecology and decided to devote his whole life to the science. 他开始研究生态学,并决心将他的一生献身于这门学科。 4. The college graduated 50 students from the science department last year. 这所学院去年有50名理科毕业生。', '形容词: scientific');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('without', '[wɪ\'ðaʊt]', 'prep.没有；无；在外面 adv.在缺乏的情况下；在外面 conj.除非', '1. Without the sun, nothing would grow. 没有太阳，就不会有生物。 2. It is hard to sleep without a cooler in this room. 没有空气调节器，在这间屋里很难入睡。 3. I just want an ordinary car without the frills. 我只要一辆没有多余装饰的普通汽车。 4. The rumor was without foundation. 那条谣言毫无根据。 5. Never mind, we can manage without. 不要紧，没有也能对付。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `npee` VALUES ('snatch', '[snætʃ]', 'n.抢夺；一阵；一点点 v.夺取；抓住', '1. The thief made a snatch at the woman\'s purse. 小偷试图抢夺那妇女的钱包。 2. He made a brave snatch at victory but failed. 他奋力争取胜利，但是失败了。 3. He has a snatch of sleep sitting in his chair. 他坐在椅子里稍睡片刻。 4. They put the snatch on him for a cut of the take. 他们强要他分给他们一分。 5. He snatched up his gun and fired. 他突然拿起枪来射击。', '名词: snatcher 过去式: snatched 过去分词: snatched 现在分词: snatching 第三人称单数: snatches');
